INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('farce', '[fɑːrs]', 'n.闹剧；胡闹；滑稽戏 v.添加笑料；填充', '1. Their negotiations were a farce since their leaders had already made the decision. 他们的谈判简直就是一场荒唐的笑剧，因为他们的领导们早就作出决定了。 2. It seemed to be a farce and it made us doubled up with laugher. 它看起来很像闹剧，我们都笑弯了腰。 3. The trials were a mere farce since no judges were present at all. 这些审判简直是胡闹，因为根本没有法官出席。 4. The play suddenly changes from farce to tragedy. 这部戏突然从闹剧变成悲剧。', '过去式: farced 过去分词: farced 现在分词: farcing 第三人称单数: farces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pivotal', '[\'pɪvətl]', 'adj.重要的；关键的；轴的', '1. It was a pivotal moment in her life. 那是她一生中重要的时刻。 2. Stomach is the pivotal organ of digestive system. 胃是重要的消化系统器官之一。 3. Love plays a pivotal role on out life. 爱在我们的生活中扮演重要的角色。 4. Standards are pivotal to the success of digital wallets. 标准化是数字钱包能否成功的关键。', '副词: pivotally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('folklore', '[\'foʊklɔːr]', 'n.民间传说；民俗学；民间风俗', '1. Rumors of their antics became part of the folklore of Hollywood. 他们滑稽动作的传闻成了好莱坞民间传说的一部分。 2. The singer devoted his whole life in study of the folklore in the northwest part of China. 这位歌手终生致力于研究中国西北部的民间传说。 3. In the United States, however, the field of folklore is relatively new. 但在美国，民俗学却是一门新兴的学科。 4. The essay aims to tackle the inner mechanism of Xu\'s novels from the point view of folklore. 摘要本文从民俗学角度阐释妈祖文化对许地山创作的影响。', '形容词: folkloric 名词: folklorist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('metropolis', '[mə\'trɑːpəlɪs]', 'n.大都市；重要中心；首府', '1. New York is the metropolis of North America. 纽约是北美的大都市。 2. This was a great, pleasing metropolis after all. 这毕竟是个令人振奋的大都市。 3. The former appealed to Corcyra, which was the metropolis of Epidamnus. 民主者向伊庇丹努的首府科西拉求助。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('converse', '[kən\'vɜːrs]', 'n.相反的事物；逆命题 adj.相反的；逆向的；倒的 v.交谈；谈话 n.谈话', '1. He says she is satisfied, but I believe the converse to be true: she is very dissatisfied. 他说她已心满意足了，不过我认为实际情况相反: 她很不满意。 2. I believe the converse of what you are saying. 我相信的和你说的正相反。 3. It is possible, of course, that the converse of this theory may also be true. 当然该原理的逆命题也有可能成立。 4. This statement is converse to that one. 这个声明和那个相反。 5. Would you give me half an hour to converse with you? 我想跟你谈谈，半小时就行。 6. It is a pleasure to converse with her. 和她谈话是一种乐趣。', '副词: conversely 过去式: conversed 过去分词: conversed 现在分词: conversing 第三人称单数: converses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('guarantee', '[ˌɡærən\'tiː]', 'n.保证；保证书；担保；担保人；抵押品 vt.保证；担保', '1. A diploma is no guarantee of efficiency. 持有文凭不能保证工作效率一定高。 2. I guarantee that this will not happen again. 我保证此类事情不会再发生。 3. We guarantee the fastness of these dyes. 我们担保这些染料不褪色。 4. He put up his house as a guarantee. 他提供房子作为担保。 5. A diploma is no guarantee of efficiency. 持有文凭不能保证工作效率一定高。', '过去式: guaranteed 过去分词: guaranteed 现在分词: guaranteeing 第三人称单数: guarantees');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cognition', '[kɑːɡ\'nɪʃn]', 'n.认识；认识力；认知', '1. It is a leap in the process of cognition. 这是认识过程的一次飞跃。 2. People have speculated about human cognition for 2000 years. 人们对人类的认知力已思索了2000年。 3. A cognition is an immanent act of mind. 认知是头脑的内在活动。 4. Emotions are not tools of cognition. 情绪并不能作为认知的工具。', '形容词: cognitional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bow', '[baʊ]', 'n.弓；鞠躬礼；蝴蝶结；船头 v.鞠躬；致敬；压弯', '1. At that time, people hunt with bows and arrows. 在那时,人们以弓﹑ 箭行猎。 2. He moved aside for her with a polite bow. 他礼貌地鞠躬，退避一旁让她过去。 3. She has a dress decorated with bows. 她有一条饰有蝴蝶结的连衣裙。 4. My little sister can tie shoelaces in a bow. 我妹妹能把鞋带打成蝴蝶结。 5. The cast bowed as the audience applauded. 演员们向鼓掌的观众鞠躬。', '过去式: bowed 过去分词: bowed 现在分词: bowing 第三人称单数: bows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vein', '[veɪn]', 'n.静脉；纹理；叶脉；岩脉 vt.使有脉络；用脉络装饰', '1. The doctor injects glucose into the patient\'s vein. 医生把葡萄糖注射入病人的静脉。 2. The selection of a suitable vein model is the key for vein analysis. 摘要选用适用的纹理模型是进行纹理分析的关键。 3. Ginkgo biloba leaf petiole, is actually composed of many vein from the collection of vascular bundle group. 银杏叶的叶柄，实际上是由许多叶脉集合而成的维管束群。', '形容词: veinal 过去式: veined 过去分词: veined 现在分词: veining 第三人称单数: veins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lipid', '[\'lɪpɪd]', 'n.脂质；油脂', '1. The blood plasma lipid examination was abnormal. 血浆脂质出现不同程度的异常变化。 2. This results in accumulation of a sticky lipid called ceramide. 这导致了称为神经酰胺的粘性脂质聚集。 3. This is one of the most widely used tests for evaluating the extent of lipid oxidation. 这是衡量油脂氧化程度的应用最广泛的试验之一。 4. Dietary fiber would also benefit people with hypercholesterolemia because of its possible lipid lowering effect. 膳食纤维对血胆脂醇过多的人也有好处，因为它能降低人体内的油脂含量。', '形容词: lipidic 异体字: lipide');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tractable', '[\'træktəbl]', 'adj.（正式）易驾驭的', '1. Gold and silver are tractable metals. 金和银是容易加工的金属。 2. Stener had always been very tractable. 斯坦纳总是容易对付的。 3. They are mighty sagacious, tractable creature. 它们都是十分伶俐，十分容易驾驭的动物。', '副词: tractably 名词: tractability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('puncture', '[\'pʌŋktʃər]', 'n.刺穿；刺孔 v.刺穿；削弱', '1. Some cyclists carry repair outfits in case they have a puncture. 有些骑自行车的人带修理工具，以防车胎被刺破。 2. He demonstrated how to mend a puncture. 他示范如何修补车胎刺孔。 3. Our tires do not puncture easily. 我们的轮胎不易爆破。 4. I wish something would happen to puncture her ego. 我希望让她碰个钉子。', '形容词: puncturable 过去式: punctured 过去分词: punctured 现在分词: puncturing 第三人称单数: punctures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glare', '[ɡler]', 'n.闪耀光；刺眼 v.发眩光；瞪视', '1. I like turning a corner from the shade of a house into the full torrid glare of an open space. 我喜欢将来自房子的色度的一个角落变成开着空间的完整晒焦的闪耀光。 2. These sunglasses are designed to reduce glare. 这些太阳镜是为减少刺眼的强光而设计的。 3. The glare of the oncoming headlights temporarily blinded me. 迎面车灯刺眼的光照得我瞬间什么也看不见。 4. Eyelashes defend the eye by shading it from glare. 眼睫毛通过遮掩眼睛而使眼睛避免受眩光刺激。', '过去式: glared 过去分词: glared 现在分词: glaring 第三人称单数: glares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sled', '[sled]', 'n.<美>雪撬', '1. Sled pulled by dog is in common use in the Arctic. 狗拉的雪橇在北极地区很常用。 2. A logging sled. 滑板中耕机 3. Jack dug his sled out of the cellar. 杰克在地窑里找到了他的雪橇。 4. The man attached a strong rope to his sled. 那人将一条结实的绳子系在他的雪撬上。', '名词: sledder 过去式: sledded 过去分词: sledded 现在分词: sledding 第三人称单数: sleds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pedagogy', '[\'pedəɡɑːdʒi]', 'n.教育学；教授法；教育', '1. Paulo Freire is a representative of the Pedagogy of the Oppressed. 摘要弗莱雷是被压迫教育学的代表人物。 2. Narrative pedagogy is unending converging conversations. 叙述教育学是无穷尽的聚合交谈。 3. Phenomenological pedagogy calls for the rediscovery and return of human spirits in educational practice. 现象学教育学呼唤教育实践之人文精神的重新发现与回归。 4. After critical consideration on the anti-essentialism in pedagogy, we should seek certainty in the new era. 基于反本质主义教育学主张的批判性反思，我国教育学研究需要在具体的教育情境中追求确定性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hive', '[haɪv]', 'n.蜂房；蜂箱；蜂群；喧闹繁忙的场所 vi.蜂进入蜂箱；聚居；把一部分分离出来 vt.使蜂入箱；储备', '1. A hive cannot exist without a queen. 蜂房不可无蜂王。 2. There were so many bees in the hive that I felt great fear. 蜂房里有那么多蜜蜂我感到很害怕。 3. Tapping on the hive excited the bees. 轻拍蜂箱触动了蜜蜂。 4. He built a special hive,containing only one honeycomb. 他特制了一个只有一个蜂窝的蜂箱。 5. Tom has hived off again. 汤姆又不辞而别了。', '过去式: hived 过去分词: hived 现在分词: hiving 第三人称单数: hives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trepidation', '[ˌtrepɪ\'deɪʃn]', 'n.恐惧；惊惶；忧虑；颤抖', '1. They kept dumb in fear and trepidation. 他们诚惶诚恐一言不发。 2. The threat of an epidemic caused great alarm and trepidation. 流行病猖獗因而人心惶惶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('terrify', '[\'terɪfaɪ]', 'v.使害怕；使恐怖；威胁', '1. Or will carelessness or corruption allow the theft of a nuclear device to terrify us all? 会不会由于安全部门的疏忽或腐败，让恐怖分子得到核装置用来威胁民众？', '过去式: terrified 过去分词: terrified 现在分词: terrifying 第三人称单数: terrifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skillful', '[\'skɪlfəl]', 'adj.熟练的；灵巧的', '1. His skillful manipulation vivified this puppet. 他熟练的操作让木偶栩栩如生。 2. He is a skillful English-speaking professor. 他是位英语讲得很熟练的教授。 3. Her skillful fingers spun the wool out to a fine thread. 她那灵巧的手指把羊毛纺织成了细线。 4. With a skillful movement he rounded the small fishing-boat. 他以灵巧的动作使小渔船调过头来。', '副词: skillfully 名词: skillfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adore', '[ə\'dɔːr]', 'vt.爱慕；崇拜；很喜欢', '1. Men can only adore women who are adorable. 男人们只爱慕那些让人爱慕的女人。 2. The kids adore their father and confide in him. 孩子们崇拜并信赖他们的父亲。 3. The boys adore their mothers. 男孩们敬慕他们的母亲。 4. All the girls in our school adore the handsome mathematics teacher who happens to be a bachelor. 我们学校里所有女孩子都崇拜那个恰巧是单身汉的英俊数学老师。', '副词: adoringly 名词: adorer 过去式: adored 过去分词: adored 现在分词: adoring 第三人称单数: adores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deprecate', '[\'deprəkeɪt]', 'v.声明不赞成；抨击；反对', '1. The peace-loving people deprecate war. 爱好和平的人民反对战争。', '副词: deprecatingly 名词: deprecation 过去式: deprecated 过去分词: deprecated 现在分词: deprecating 第三人称单数: deprecates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obscure', '[əb\'skjʊr]', 'adj.难解的；不著名的；微暗的；[语音学]轻音的 v.使 ... 模糊；隐藏；变模糊 n.模糊不清的东西', '1. The rules for the competition are somewhat obscure. 比赛的规则有点让人费解。 2. The reasons why he did it are obscure. 他做那事的理由还不清楚。 3. The report had been published in an obscure German journal. 这个报道刊登在德国一家不著名的报纸上。 4. He set the bed in an obscure corner. 他把床放在一个昏暗的角落。 5. The moon was obscured by clouds. 月亮被云遮住了。 6. Hence things whichhave perplexed you and made the case more obscure have served to enlighten meand to strengthen my conclusions. 因此，那些使你们大惑不解并且使案情更加模糊不清的事物，却会对我有所启发，并且能加强我的论断。', '副词: obscurely 比较级: obscurer 最高级: obscurest 名词: obscureness 过去式: obscured 过去分词: obscured 现在分词: obscuring 第三人称单数: obscures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mechanic', '[mə\'kænɪk]', 'n.技工；机修工 adj.手工的；（使用）机械的', '1. He worked in a garage as a mechanic. 他在汽车修理厂当技工。 2. The foreman laid out the job for the new mechanic. 领班对新来的技工说明了工作任务。 3. That young man is a motor mechanic. 那个年轻人是一个汽车修理工。 4. The mechanic drained all the oil from the engine. 机械工将发动机中的油全部放走。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('landmass', '[\'lændmæs]', 'n.大陆；大片陆地', '1. Antarctica is the earth\'s coldest landmass. 南极洲是地球上最冷的大陆。 2. Asia and Europe form a huge landmass. 亚洲和欧洲连成一片大陆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solution', '[sə\'luːʃn]', 'n.解决办法；解答；溶液；溶解；设计', '1. He reasoned out a solution to the problem. 他经过推断,找出了解决问题的办法。 2. We haven\'t found the solution yet, but I\'m sure we\'re on the right track. 我们还没有找到解决办法，但我肯定我们的思路是对的。 3. The solution of the problem has just come to me. 我刚想起如何解答这个问题。 4. What color is copper sulphate solution? 硫酸铜溶液是什么颜色？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confound', '[kən\'faʊnd]', 'vt.使困惑；混淆；挫败；诅咒', '1. Don\'t confound the means with the ends. 不要把手段和目的混淆起来。 2. To confound two things means not to be able to tell them apart. 混淆两件事物的意思是说没能把它们区分开来。', '名词: confounder 过去式: confounded 过去分词: confounded 现在分词: confounding 第三人称单数: confounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('admit', '[əd\'mɪt]', 'vt.承认；允许进入；给…进入的权利；容纳 vi.承认；允许进入；允许', '1. He made a terrible mistake, but he refused to admit it. 他犯了一个严重的错误,可是他拒不承认。 2. We have to admit that there is still room for improvement. 我们不得不承认,在这方面有尚待改进的地方。 3. Each ticket admits two people to the party. 每张票可供两人入场参加聚会。 4. I reluctantly admitted to being nervous about the test. 我勉强承认我对测试感到紧张。', '过去式: admitted 过去分词: admitted 现在分词: admitting 第三人称单数: admits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flip', '[flɪp]', 'vt.掷；轻击；弹 vi.翻转 n.（跳水或体操动作中的）空翻；轻弹；浏览 adj.无礼的；冒失的；轻率的', '1. Let\'s flip a coin to see who goes first. 我们来掷硬币看谁先去。 2. Kids flip frisbees while their elders chat. 孩子们玩飞盘，大人聊天。 3. He flipped a crumb across the room. 他把面包屑弹到房间另一头。 4. She flipped the insect from her face. 她将昆虫从脸上弹掉。 5. He flipped to a fresh page and began to write. 他翻到另外一页,开始写了起来。 6. The gymnast had to do a double back flip. 这个体操运动员得做一个360度后空翻。 7. Don\'t be flip with me. 不要对我油腔滑舌。', '比较级: flipper 最高级: flippest 过去式: flipped 过去分词: flipped 现在分词: flipping 第三人称单数: flips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boom', '[buːm]', 'n.繁荣；兴旺；激增；低沉声 n.帆杠；吊杆；支臂；尾桁；水栅 vi.急速增长；发出低沉声 vt.使兴旺；促进', '1. It\'s a boom year this year. 今年是繁荣昌盛的一年。 2. He made his pile during the property boom. 在房地产生意兴隆期间他发了大财。 3. The oil market is enjoying a boom. 石油市场欣欣向荣。 4. City growth far outran the general population boom. 城市的发展大大超过总的人口激增。 5. The boom swung over the deck. 帆杠在甲板上转动。 6. Business is booming. 商业正日趋繁荣。 7. Foreign investments boomed the city. 国外投资使这个城市迅速繁荣起来。', '过去式: boomed 过去分词: boomed 现在分词: booming 第三人称单数: booms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incinerate', '[ɪn\'sɪnəreɪt]', 'v.焚化(废物)；烧成灰；火化', '1. The flames of my rage will incinerate you! 我的怒火将把你熔为灰烬! 2. Incinerate can now be turned on or off. 烧弃现在能够被选择关闭或开启。 3. YesAttack1 - \"I\'ll incinerate them. \" -我来把他们烧成灰烬。 4. Glyph of Incinerate: Increases damage of Incinerate by 5%. 烧尽雕文：提升烧尽的伤害5%25。', '名词: incineration 过去式: incinerated 过去分词: incinerated 现在分词: incinerating 第三人称单数: incinerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('represent', '[ˌreprɪ\'zent]', 'vt.表现；表示；描绘；代表；象征；说明；阐明 vi.提出异议', '1. Monsters in dreams often represent fears. 怪物在梦里经常表现为恐惧。 2. Both represent the triumph of passion over reason. 两者都表现出理智之外的激情。 3. Dotted arrows represent flow of information. 虚矢线表示信息流程。 4. You must represent your complaints to Head Office. 你必须向总部表示出你的抱怨。', '形容词: representable 名词: representability 过去式: represented 过去分词: represented 现在分词: representing 第三人称单数: represents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('artistic', '[ɑːr\'tɪstɪk]', 'adj.艺术的', '1. She has artistic tendencies. 她有艺术气质。 2. We are disciples of the artistic leader. 我们是那位艺术领袖的追随者。 3. He is a man with an artistic temperament. 他是个有艺术家气质的男子。 4. Our artistic director was instrumental in persuading the orchestra to come. 我们的艺术指导帮助请来管弦乐队。', '副词: artistically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impure', '[ɪm\'pjʊr]', 'adj.不纯的；肮脏的；渎神的', '1. He took a shot of impure heroin. 他注射不纯的海洛因。 2. The air of a big city is often impure. 大城市的空气往往是污浊的。 3. You have impure thoughts. 你的思想真肮脏。 4. In some religions pork is considered impure. 某些宗教认为猪肉是亵渎的。', '副词: impurely 比较级: impurer 最高级: impurest 名词: impureness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intervene', '[ˌɪntər\'viːn]', 'vi.干涉；干预；介入；调停；插入；阻挠', '1. Don\'t intervene in the affairs of another country. 不要干涉别的国家的事务。 2. It\'s time that men of good sense and good will to intervene. 这该是那些头脑清醒和心地善良的人们出面干预的时候了。 3. You\'d better not intervene in their dispute. 你最好还是不要介入他们的争端。 4. I am powerless to intervene in the matter. 我对调停此事无能为力。', '形容词: interventional 名词: intervenor 过去式: intervened 过去分词: intervened 现在分词: intervening 第三人称单数: intervenes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perilous', '[\'perələs]', 'adj.危险的；冒险的', '1. The snow and the blackout combined to make motoring perilous. 大雪加上灯火管制使得车辆行驶成了危险的事。 2. Whoever bars others from revolution will find himself in a very perilous position. 凡是不准人家革命，那是很危险的。', '副词: perilously 名词: perilousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('planet', '[\'plænɪt]', 'n.行星', '1. The Earth is a planet. 地球是一颗行星。 2. Mars is the fourth planet in order from the sun. 火星是太阳系的第四颗行星。 3. They claimed to have discovered a new planet. 他们宣称发现了一颗新的行星。 4. It is the only planet that we know harbors life. 它是我们所知唯一适合生物生存的行星。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('competent', '[\'kɑːmpɪtənt]', 'adj.有能力的；足够的；胜任的', '1. Her drawing is competent, but her composition is poor. 她的画有功力，但布局欠佳。 2. She was declared mentally competent to stand trial. 她被宣告有接受审判的精神能力。 3. He is competent enough to fill that position. 他完全胜任那个职位。 4. Is Mary competent as a teacher? 玛丽胜任教师的工作吗？', '副词: competently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intrepid', '[ɪn\'trepɪd]', 'adj.无畏的；刚毅的', '1. He is not really satisfied with his intrepid action. 他没有真正满意他的无畏行动。 2. Some intrepid individuals were still prepared to make the journey. 某些无畏的人仍然准备作此旅行。 3. He has an intrepid disposition, and great strength. 他生性悍勇,力大过人。 4. Lately, though, an intrepid band of researchers has been trying to remedy that. 而近来一些坚韧不拔的研究者一直试图在修正那种探索。', '副词: intrepidly 名词: intrepidity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detach', '[dɪ\'tætʃ]', 'vt.使分离；拆卸；派遣 [计算机] 脱离.', '1. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。 2. I tried to detach myself from the reality of these terrible events. 我尽力使自己从这些可怕事件的现实中摆脱出来。 3. We should detach good apples from bad. 我们必须把好的苹果与坏的分开. 4. He detached a link from a chain. 他从链子上拆下一个链环。', '形容词: detachable 副词: detachably 名词: detachability 过去式: detached 过去分词: detached 现在分词: detaching 第三人称单数: detaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reimburse', '[ˌriːɪm\'bɜːrs]', 'vt.偿还；报销', '1. I was reimbursed in full. 我已得到全部补偿。 2. We will reimburse the customer for any loss or damage. 我们将赔偿顾客所受到的一切损失和损害。 3. The company will reimburse you for travel expenses. 公司会为你报销差旅费。 4. All expenses will be reimbursed to you. 一切费用都能给你报销。', '形容词: reimbursable 名词: reimbursement 过去式: reimbursed 过去分词: reimbursed 现在分词: reimbursing 第三人称单数: reimburses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('speculate', '[\'spekjuleɪt]', 'vt.推测 vi.投机；深思', '1. The doctors speculate that he died of cancer. 医生推测他死于癌症。 2. Can you speculate how such damage might arise? 你能否想出这种伤害是怎样引起的? 3. He likes to speculate on the stock market. 他喜欢炒股。 4. It\'s dangerous to speculate. 做投机买卖是很危险的。', '过去式: speculated 过去分词: speculated 现在分词: speculating 第三人称单数: speculates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('congruity', '[kən\'gruːətɪ]', 'n.适合；一致；调和', '1. There is congruity and appropriateness in this inseparable link. 这不可分开的关系，是适宜的，是对称的。 2. There is a definite congruity in the candidates\' approach to the tax problem. 候选人在对待税收问题的态度上有着明确的共同之处。 3. Congruity is the mother of love. 和谐是爱情之母。', '名词复数: congruities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('postpone', '[poʊ\'spoʊn]', 'vt.延期；推迟', '1. The weather being bad, we had to postpone our trip. 因为天气不好,我们不得不延期出行。 2. She did not postpone her departure. 她不再延迟她的行期。 3. Can we postpone the meeting till tomorrow? 我们可以把会议延到明天吗? 4. The commander decided to postpone the big push until the spring. 指挥官决定把大规模的进攻推迟到春天进行。', '形容词: postponable 名词: postponement 过去式: postponed 过去分词: postponed 现在分词: postponing 第三人称单数: postpones');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oral', '[\'ɔːrəl]', 'adj.口头的；口部的；口语的 n.口试', '1. The old man told us a story passed on by oral tradition. 老人给我们讲述了一个口头流传的故事。 2. We hurried an oral agreement before signing a formal contract. 在签正式合同之前，我们先草签了一份口头协议。 3. He gave us an oral report after inspecting the factory. 视察了那家工厂后,他给我们作了口头汇报。 4. Enteric viruses are able to enter in the body via the oral route. 肠道病毒是经口进入人体的。 5. He failed the oral. 他口试不及格。', '副词: orally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resource', '[\'riːsɔːrs]', 'n.资源；机敏；才略；寄托；消遣', '1. If I may refer back to the problem we discussed, I think we shall stress on the conservation of our natural resource. 请允许我重提我们刚才讨论过的问题，我想我们应该强调保存我们的自然资源。 2. Resources management is an important business skill. 资源管理是一项重要的经营技能。 3. He is a man of great resource. 他是一个足智多谋的人。 4. The job called for all my resources of energy and patience. 这项工作需要我拿出自己的全部精力和耐性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lime', '[laɪm]', 'n.石灰；粘鸟胶 n.酸橙；酸橙树 vt.施石灰；涂上粘性物质；沾上粘鸟胶 adj.石灰的', '1. He added some water into the lime. 他往石灰里加了些水。 2. We spread lime where the soil was sour. 土壤酸性大的地方我们就撒上石灰。 3. This lime curry is particularly hot . 这酸橙咖喱菜非常辣。 4. A broad avenue of lime trees led up to a grand entrance with huge oak doors. 一条栽有酸橙树的宽阔林阴道通向巨大的橡木门的雄伟入口。 5. Lime water may be bought at any druggist\'s, or easily prepared at home. 石灰水可从药店购得，不过在家里配制也很容易。', '形容词: limy 过去式: limed 过去分词: limed 现在分词: liming 第三人称单数: limes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cuisine', '[kwɪ\'ziːn]', 'n.烹饪；佳肴', '1. Chinese cuisine is very different from European. 中国烹饪与欧洲烹饪有很大区别。 2. I studied Greek cuisine for one year. 我学了一年的希腊菜烹饪法。 3. After that, they might end their day dining in a restaurant that serves Chinese cuisine. 然后他俩可能会去一家中国餐馆吃晚饭，以此来结束一天的活动。 4. The hotel restaurant is noted for its excellent cuisine. 这家旅馆的餐厅以美味佳肴闻名遐迩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diversify', '[daɪ\'vɜːrsɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使多样化；使变化；使不同 vi.多样化', '1. We were told to diversify our portfolio. 我们被告知我们的投资组合需多样化。 2. We must try to diversify the syllabus to attract more students. 我们应该使教学大纲内容多样化 3. I want to diversify my experience and broaden my view sight. 我想丰富阅历，开阔视野。 4. Hill and woods diversify the landscape. 山陵和树林点缀景色。 5. A factory must try to diversify for further development. 一个工厂要获得进一步发展就要努力使产品多样化。', '名词: diversification 过去式: diversified 过去分词: diversified 现在分词: diversifying 第三人称单数: diversifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tuition', '[tu\'ɪʃn]', 'n.学费；教诲；教学', '1. The money is sufficient to cover the tuition. 这笔钱够付学费。 2. She relies on her parents for tuition. 她的学费依赖于父母。 3. Thank you for your tuition. 谢谢您的教诲。 4. Mary has derived a lot of benefit from her tuition. 玛丽从她的教学中得到很大收益。', '形容词: tuitional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trait', '[treɪt]', 'n.特征；特点；少许；一笔', '1. They suddenly exhibit a striking new trait. 它们突然呈现出一种新的显著特征。 2. One of his less attractive traits is criticizing his wife in public. 他有个不大讨人喜欢的特点，就是爱当众责备妻子。 3. Our CEO talks and behaves without a trait of authority. 我们公司的首席执行官言行举止没有一点官气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devotion', '[dɪ\'voʊʃn]', 'n.虔诚；献身；奉献；热爱', '1. Through great effort perhaps he is just cultivating a little devotion. 尽管经过了很大的努力，他也许只是培养出少许的虔诚。 2. We were deeply moved by their devotion. 我们为他们的献身精神所感动。 3. His devotion to science is well known. 他对科学的献身精神为人熟知。 4. His devotion led him to the priesthood. 他的信仰使他成为祭司。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conspire', '[kən\'spaɪər]', 'v.阴谋；协力；共谋，串通一气', '1. They conspire against the government. 他们阴谋推翻政府。 2. But if any force tries to conspire and work against the people\'s will, we might be compelled to take that way despite our unwillingness. 但是如果有人试图搞阴谋反对人民的意愿，那么我们将被迫做我们不愿做的事。', '副词: conspiringly 名词: conspirer 过去式: conspired 过去分词: conspired 现在分词: conspiring 第三人称单数: conspires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('levy', '[\'levi]', 'n.征税；召集 vt.征收；发动 vi.强收', '1. The basis of the proposals is a levy of 0.25 per cent. 建议的征税基点为百分之零点二五。 2. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 3. The government has decided to levy a tax on import cars. 政府决定征收进口汽车税。 4. The nation levied all able-bodied man for the war. 国家征召所有壮丁参战。 5. The court may have to levy on your estate to pay your debts. 法庭可能不得不扣押你的房地产，用来偿付你的债务。', '名词: levier 名词复数: levies 过去式: levied 过去分词: levied 现在分词: levying 第三人称单数: levies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('raze', '[reɪz]', 'v.夷为平地；摧毁；消除；抹去', '1. The city was razed by an earthquake. 地震把这个城市夷为平地。 2. The troops attacked his village and razed it to the ground. 军队攻击了他的村子，把村子夷为平地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('occasional', '[ə\'keɪʒənl]', 'adj.偶然的；临时的；不时的', '1. He\'s someone I have an occasional chat and joke with. 我偶然跟他闲聊，一起说笑话。 2. An occasional outburst of anger creates wrinkles on the face. 一次愤怒的偶然爆发会在脸部产生皱纹。 3. All in a occasional chance, he got the out-of-print book in a secondhand bookstore. 纯粹由于偶然的机会，他在一家二手书店里找到了那本绝版的书. 4. He is only an occasional workman. 他只是个临时雇工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('loot', '[luːt]', 'n.掠夺品；赃物；<俚>钱 v.掠夺；洗劫', '1. I sneaked a loot at the plans on her desk. 我偷偷地看了一眼她书桌上的计划。 2. During the riot there are ten cases of loot and two cases of arsons. 在暴乱中有10起抢劫案和两起纵火案。 3. The thieves divides the loot into equal shares. 窃贼们把赃物均分成若干份。 4. The thieves were caught with their loot by the police. 警察抓获了小偷及其赃物。 5. The Japanese soldiers looted and massacred for three days in Nanjing. 日本兵在南京掠夺屠杀了三天。', '名词: looter 过去式: looted 过去分词: looted 现在分词: looting 第三人称单数: loots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mass', '[mæs]', 'n.大量；块；众多 adj.大规模的；群众的 v.集中 Mass. n.弥撒曲；弥撒', '1. After harvest we will have a mass of rice. 秋收后，我们将获得大量稻谷。 2. There were masses of dark clouds in the sky. 天上有朵朵乌云。 3. Football stars seem larger-than-life to the mass of fans. 在众多的球迷看来,足球明星是十分杰出的。 4. Modern education is a mass enterprise. 现代教育是一项大规模的企业。 5. Crowds massed along the road where the king would pass. 群众聚集在国王要经过的街道旁。 6. The priest sings Mass. 牧师吟唱弥撒曲。', '过去式: massed 过去分词: massed 现在分词: massing 第三人称单数: masses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indemnity', '[ɪn\'demnəti]', 'n.保证；赔偿；保险', '1. The bank can issue a letter of indemnity to the shipper. 银行可向承运人出具保证函。 2. He have to pay an indemnity of&100. 他必须支付100英镑的赔偿。 3. The victorious nations are demanding huge indemnities from their former enemies. 战胜国要求战败国交付巨额赔款。 4. Indemnity can be deducted from the salary of laborer. 赔偿金额可以从劳动者的工资扣除。', '名词复数: indemnities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swing', '[swɪŋ]', 'n.摇摆；改变；冲力；秋千 v.摇摆；旋转；动摇', '1. The swing of the ship made many people seasick. 船的摇摆使许多人晕船。 2. The willow branches swing in the breeze. 柳枝迎风摇摆。 3. I used to swing, but then age and good taste overtook me. 我原来喜欢赶时髦，后来随着年龄的增长和审美观的改变便不再那样了。 4. Tiny changes here can be felt in the backswing and lead to big improvements in the hit swing. 这里在后摆时能够感受出来的很小的改变就可以让你在击球摆动上得到很大的进步。 5. This will swing public opinions against the government. 这将使公共舆论转而反对政府。', '形容词: swingy 过去式: swung 过去分词: swung 现在分词: swinging 第三人称单数: swings');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diplomacy', '[dɪ\'ploʊməsi]', 'n.外交', '1. He refined the whole art of shuttle diplomacy. 他把穿梭外交艺术提高到炉火纯青的地步。 2. This is as true of warfare as it is of diplomacy. 这是真正的战争，就像刚才提到的外交。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circumscribe', '[\'sɜːrkəmskraɪb]', 'v.限制；划一条线包围；确定...的范围；画（几何图形的）外接圆', '1. Do not circumscribe your study only in classes. 不要把自己的学习只局限于课堂。 2. A man should not circumscribe his activity by any inflexible fence of rigid rules. 人不应该将自己的行为限制在由僵化的条文构成的不可变通的范围之内。 3. Please circumscribe the words which are wrongly spelled. 请将拼错的词圈出来。 4. First, it is always possible to circumscribe a sphere in a camera-aligned quad. 首先，它总能保证和一个与摄像机对齐的矩形相切。', '形容词: circumscribable 名词: circumscriber 过去式: circumscribed 过去分词: circumscribed 现在分词: circumscribing 第三人称单数: circumscribes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genial', '[\'dʒiːniəl]', 'adj.友好的；(气候)温暖的', '1. Her genial smile made every guest feel at home. 她亲切的笑容使每个人都感觉宾至如归。 2. The man was so genial that I was drawn to him at once. 他这么和蔼，我立刻为他着迷。 3. The Nankun Mountain with a genial climate is an ideal holiday resort. 气候宜人的南昆山是一处度假胜地。 4. The genial warmth of the sun around the door appeared somewhat human. 门周围温暖柔和的阳光仿佛人一样温情脉脉。', '副词: genially 名词: geniality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cause', '[kɔːz]', 'vt.引起；使发生 n.原因；理由；事业', '1. Smoking can cause lung cancer. 吸烟可致肺癌。 2. She is always causing trouble for people. 她总是给人添麻烦。 3. Police are investigating the causes of the explosion. 警方正在调查爆炸的原因。 4. You have no cause for complaint. 你没有理由抱怨。', '形容词: causable 名词: causer 过去式: caused 过去分词: caused 现在分词: causing 第三人称单数: causes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adventure', '[əd\'ventʃər]', 'n.冒险；奇遇 vt.冒险；尝试 vi.冒险；大胆进行', '1. To the well-organized mind, death is but the next great adventure. 中文的意思是,对于一个理性极其成熟的人来说,死亡仅仅是下一个伟大冒险。 2. No matter how hard he tried, he couldn\'t persuade his friends to give up the adventure. 无论他怎么努力,都不能说服他的朋友们放弃冒险。 3. He\'s sailed the seven seas in search of adventure. 他闯荡七大洋去历险。 4. The man ventures his life in space exploration. 这个人冒着生命危险探索宇宙空间。 5. It is foolish to haphazardly adventure. 随便冒险是愚蠢的。', '过去式: adventured 过去分词: adventured 现在分词: adventuring 第三人称单数: adventures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exile', '[\'ekzaɪl]', 'n.放逐；流放；被放逐者 vt.放逐；流放', '1. The king was sent into exile. 国王遭到放逐。 2. He was publicly disgraced and sent into exile. 他被当众贬谪，放逐异乡。 3. Everyone is born king,and most people die in exile. 每个人生下来都是王，而大多数人却在放逐中死去。 4. Exile was for him a living death. 他遭流放是进了活地狱。 5. He was exiled from the country for one year. 他被放逐一年。', '形容词: exilic 过去式: exiled 过去分词: exiled 现在分词: exiling 第三人称单数: exiles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exalt', '[ɪɡ\'zɔːlt]', 'v.赞扬；提升；加强', '1. All the people of whom you and I are the rag-tag and bobtail, all the camp followers of western civilization, we have taken it for granted that even if we did not live up to those exalted ethical standards, we did a great deal better than anyone else. 我们所有的人，包括你和我这样的下层平民，以及所有西方文明的依附者都认为，即使我们尚未达到那些崇高的道德标准，我们也还是是比别的任何人都干得好得多。 2. He was exalted to the position of general manager. 他被提升到总经理的职位。', '名词: exalter 过去式: exalted 过去分词: exalted 现在分词: exalting 第三人称单数: exalts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('upright', '[\'ʌpraɪt]', 'adj.直立的；垂直的；正直的 adv.垂直地 n.垂直；竖立；竖钢琴', '1. Only humans have a natural upright posture. 只有人类才有自然直立的姿势。 2. Please put the back of your seat in an upright position. 请把座位靠背转到垂直位置。 3. He was a famous upright statesman. 他是一位著名的、正直的政治家。 4. Several columns among the ruins still stood upright. 在废墟中依然挺立着几根柱子。 5. The piano was nearly always an upright. 钢琴差不多总是直立式钢琴。', '副词: uprightly 名词: uprightness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mountainous', '[\'maʊntənəs]', 'adj.多山的；如山一般的', '1. He lives in a mountainous district. 他住在山区。 2. Our country is very mountainous. 我国是一个多山的国家。 3. The mountainous waves swallowed up the ship. 山一般的巨浪吞没了那艘航船。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manure', '[mə\'nʊr]', 'n.肥料 vt.施肥', '1. Animal dung may be used as manure. 动物的粪便可以作为肥料使用。 2. Tests of the manure showed a high ammonia content. 这种肥料经过化验表明氨的含量很高。 3. The peasants fertilize the field by using manure. 农民们施肥来使土地肥沃。 4. To manure land is to spread manure on it. 给土地施肥是把粪肥洒在土地上。', '形容词: manurial 名词: manurer 过去式: manured 过去分词: manured 现在分词: manuring 第三人称单数: manures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('niche', '[niːʃ]', 'n.壁龛；适当的位置；（特定产品或服务的）用户群；[生]生态龛；生态位；小生态环境 vt.放在适当的位置', '1. This is a stupa niche from the Sui Dynasty. 你看这是隋代的塔龛。 2. He found the right niche for himself. 他发现了一个适合他的职位。 3. He eventually found his niche in sports journalism. 最后他在体育新闻界找到了理想的工作。 4. Your market niche is big women. 你们的服装目标是体胖的女士。', '过去式: niched 过去分词: niched 现在分词: niching 第三人称单数: niches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compass', '[\'kʌmpəs]', 'n.圆规；指南针；范围 vt.达到；围绕；图谋', '1. Now we begin to draw a circle with compasses. 现在我们开始用圆规画一个圆。 2. I need a compass to draw a circle. 我需要一支圆规画圆。 3. A compass needle points to the north. 罗盘的指针永远指向北方。 4. The compass was invented by the Chinese, as is well known. 众所周知,指南针是中国人发明的。 5. In order to compass our object we must work hard. 为了达到我们的目标，我们必须努力工作。', '形容词: compassable 过去式: compassed 过去分词: compassed 现在分词: compassing 第三人称单数: compasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imbue', '[ɪm\'bjuː]', 'v.灌输；使感染；使充满', '1. He managed to imbue his employees with team spirit. 他成功激发起雇员的团队精神。 2. You should imbue your children with ambition to succeed 你应该使你的孩子充满希望成功的雄心。', '过去式: imbued 过去分词: imbued 现在分词: imbuing 第三人称单数: imbues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rudimentary', '[ˌruːdɪ\'mentri]', 'adj.基本的；初步的；未充分发展的', '1. They were given only rudimentary training in the job. 他们仅仅受到过基本的职业训练。 2. E-mail filters are still rudimentary cures and pretty ineffective in curtailing the deluge of unwanted messages. 电子邮件过滤软体仍旧是基本的补救方法，但对于如洪水般涌来的垃圾讯息，筛减效力实在不彰。 3. I have only a rudimentary grasp of physics. 我对物理学仅有初步的了解。 4. The robot now has several of its sensory organs attached and a rudimentary nervous system working. 机器人现在已经接上了好几个感测器，而且初步的神经系统也可以运作了。', '副词: rudimentarily 名词: rudimentariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('condensation', '[ˌkɑːnden\'seɪʃn]', 'n.浓缩；凝结；液滴', '1. A cloud is a condensation of water vapour. 云是由水蒸汽凝缩而成的。 2. The report is a brilliant condensation of several years\' work. 这报告是几年工作的精华。 3. By this means, rapid condensation takes place. 用这种方法，冷凝很快。 4. There was condensation on the windows. 玻璃窗上凝结着水珠。', '形容词: condensational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chiefly', '[\'tʃiːfli]', 'adv.主要地', '1. Air consists chiefly of nitrogen. 空气主要由氮气组成。 2. The Government is chiefly concerned with controlling inflation. 政府的当务之急是控制通货膨胀。 3. Chiefly, I asked you to remember to write to your dear mother. 我主要是想提醒你写信给你母亲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reject', '[\'riːdʒekt]', 'vt.拒绝；排斥；驳回；丢弃 n.不合格产品；被拒之人', '1. He rejected their offer of a job. 他拒绝了他们给他的工作。 2. After the transplant his body rejected the new heart. 他的身体对新移植的心脏产生了排斥作用。 3. If the application is unfounded, the people\'s court shall make an order to reject it. 申请不成立的,裁定予以驳回。 4. The supermarket rejected all spotted apples. 超级市场丢弃了所有的烂苹果。 5. The factory sells some of its better rejects cheaply, but it throws most of the rejects away. 这家公司廉价出售略好一些的次品，但将大多数次品丢弃。', '形容词: rejective 名词: rejecter 过去式: rejected 过去分词: rejected 现在分词: rejecting 第三人称单数: rejects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('register', '[\'redʒɪstər]', 'v.登记；记录；注册；挂号 n.登记簿；记录；暂存器 n.[语]语域；[音]音域通风调节设备', '1. You must register if you intend to vote. 如果你要投票选举,你就必须登记。 2. He registered the trial proceedings. 法庭速记员记录下了审判进程。 3. You must register as a member first. 你必须先注册成为会员。 4. I want this letter registered. 我想挂号邮寄这封信。 5. Would you sign the register? 请你在登记簿上签名好吗? 6. Official documents are written in formal register. 官方文件是以正式语体写成的。', '形容词: registrable 名词: registration 过去式: registered 过去分词: registered 现在分词: registering 第三人称单数: registers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fauna', '[\'fɔːnə]', 'n.（某地区或某时期的）所有动物', '1. The flora and fauna native to a geographic area. 一地理区域所固有的动植物 2. The combined flora and fauna of a region. 生物区系一地区混合的植物群与动物群 3. He studies the flora and fauna of Africa. 他研究非洲的动植物群。 4. Human beings make a strange fauna and flora. 人类是一些古怪的动植物。', '形容词: faunal 副词: faunally 名词复数: faunas');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recognition', '[ˌrekəɡ\'nɪʃn]', 'n.承认；认出；赏识', '1. Not until 1916 did the UMW finally win recognition from the anthracite operators 直到1916年，美国矿工联合会才终于得到无烟煤矿资方承认。 2. Not only are we at the forefront of electronics, but we\'ve received worldwide recognition for our advances in chemicals and engineering as well. 我们不仅处于电子技术的前沿,而且我们因在化工和工程领域的进展也得到世界范围的承认。 3. After 25 years the town centre had changed beyond all recognition. 25年过去了,市中心变得认不出来了。 4. My recognition of the face was immediate. 我一下子就认出那张面孔了。', '形容词: recognitory');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cooperation', '[koʊˌɑːpə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.合作；协作；合作社；协同作用', '1. Thanks for your cooperation. 多谢合作。 2. Our success was attributed not so much to your help as to our cooperation. 我们的成功与其归功于您的帮忙，不如归功于我们的合作。 3. We were greatly aided in our investigation by the cooperation of the police. 我们在调查的过程中得到警方的大力协助。 4. This sitcom is produced in cooperation with Hong Kong TV. 这部连续剧是同香港电视台联合制作的。', '名词: cooperationist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('neutral', '[\'nuːtrəl]', 'adj.中立的；中性的；空档的；素净色的 n.中立者；空挡位置', '1. That country remained neutral in the war. 那个国家在那场战争中保持中立。 2. He has a rather neutral character. 他品性平平。 3. When you start the engine, be sure the car is in neutral. 你在发动引擎时，一定要让汽车处于空档。 4. A neutral tie can be worn with a shirt of any colour. 暗灰色的领带配什麽颜色的衬衣都行。 5. For Britain, Switzerland was a useful and friendly neutral. 对英国来说,瑞士是一个有利和友好的中立国。', '副词: neutrally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mechanics', '[mə\'kænɪks]', 'n.力学；机械学；(技术的；操作的)过程；手法', '1. The Greek initiated the science of mechanics. 希腊人开创了力学这门科学。 2. Mechanics is taught by Dr. Hill. 力学由希尔博士教授。 3. As she grew older her hobbies included science and automobile mechanics. 随着年龄的增长，科学与自动车机械学也成了她的爱好。 4. He is studying mechanics and now he is learning all the parts of an engine. 他在学习机械学，目前正在学习引擎的所有部件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elliptical', '[ɪ\'lɪptɪkl]', 'adj.椭圆的；省略的；简要的', '1. If the satellite has an elliptical orbit, the result is a spiral wave, a miniature version of the pinwheel pattern of our galaxy. 如果卫星的轨道是椭圆的，就会产生螺旋波，就像是银河系纸风车形状的缩影。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('offhand', '[ˌɔːf\'hænd]', 'adj.即时的；未经准备的；唐突无礼的 adv.即时地；未经思索地；随便地', '1. But this offhand explanation was not strictly true. 不过这个搪塞的解释并不完全正确。 2. There was something in his offhand remarks. 他随口说出的话里倒也有些道理。 3. I don\'t like his offhand manner. 我不喜欢他那粗鲁的态度。 4. I can\'t give the answer offhand. 我不能即刻给出答复。', '副词: offhandedly 名词: offhandedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('signal', '[\'sɪɡnəl]', 'n.信号；标志 v.(发信号)通知、表示 adj.显著的', '1. A red lamp is often a danger signal. 红灯常常是危险的信号。 2. I corrected my watch by the time signal. 我按报时信号校正我的表。 3. I\'ve called several times, but I keep getting a busy signal. 我打了好几次了,可是一直是忙音。 4. We live too far from the city to get a strong television signal. 我们住的地方离城里太远, 不能收到清晰的电视图像。 5. The police signalled the traffic to move forward slowly. 警察向来往车辆打信号，示意缓慢前行。 6. People speak of Mark Twain as a signal humourous writer. 人们称马克·吐温为杰出的幽默作家。', '名词: signaler 过去式: signaled/signalled 过去分词: signaled/signalled 现在分词: signaling/signalling 第三人称单数: signals/signals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vast', '[væst]', 'adj.巨大的；广阔的', '1. That is a vast and lavish party. 那是个规模盛大、极其铺张的宴会。 2. A vast crowd turned out to watch the match. 大群的观众到场观看比赛。 3. There is always a vast chasm between rich and poor. 贫富的鸿沟始终存在。 4. The Pacific Ocean is a vast expanse of water. 太平洋是一片广大的水域。', '副词: vastly 比较级: vaster 最高级: vastest 名词: vastness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constitute', '[\'kɑːnstətuːt]', 'vt.构成；组成；任命；建立；制定', '1. Twelve months constitute one year. 十二个月构成一年。 2. Correct grammar and sentence structure do not in themselves constitute good writing. 正确的语法和句子结构本身并不能构成一篇好文章。 3. The committee is constituted of members of all three parties. 委员会由所有三个政党的成员组成。 4. He was constituted representative of the party. 他被任命为该党的代表。', '名词: constituter 过去式: constituted 过去分词: constituted 现在分词: constituting 第三人称单数: constitutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imprint', '[ɪm\'prɪnt]', 'vt.刻上记号；加特征；盖印；铭记 n.印记；痕迹；特征；印象', '1. Bette Davis will imprint her unique personality on any role she plays. 蓓蒂·戴维斯不论扮演什么角色都体现出她自己独特的性格。 2. He imprints a paper with a seal. 他在文件上盖章。 3. He tried to imprint the number on his memory. 他试图把那个号码牢牢记住 4. Only very little could escape life\'s imprint. 能逃脱生命印记的只是极少数。', '过去式: imprinted 过去分词: imprinted 现在分词: imprinting 第三人称单数: imprints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vex', '[veks]', 'vt.使恼怒；使恼火；烦扰；使困惑', '1. She was vexed at her failure. 她因失败而苦恼。 2. His silly chatter would vex you. 他那无聊的闲扯会使你烦恼。 3. His continuous chatter vexes me. 他唠叨不休，真烦死我了。 4. There was another grave problem to vex him. 还有一个使他困惑的严重问题。', '副词: vexedly 名词: vexer 过去式: vexed 过去分词: vexed 现在分词: vexing 第三人称单数: vexes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('toll', '[toʊl]', 'n.伤亡人数；钟声；通行费；代价 v.敲钟', '1. The death toll mounted (to 100). 死亡人数上升(至100). 2. The government tried to keep the death toll at a lower level. 政府力图将死亡人数控制在较低标准。 3. We heard the toll of the church bells. 我们听到了教堂大钟传来的钟声。 4. When you hear the bells toll, you\'ll know I\'m not far. 当你听到钟声，就说明我已经在附近了。 5. The church bell tolled the hour. 教堂的鸣钟报时。', '过去式: tolled 过去分词: tolled 现在分词: tolling 第三人称单数: tolls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('homing', '[\'hoʊmɪŋ]', 'adj.归巢的；回家的 n.归巢；回家 动词home的现在分词形式.', '1. Many birds have a remarkable homing instinct. 很多鸟类具有了不起的返回原地的本能。 2. Cambridge had called; he had responded like a homing pigeon. 剑桥发出了召唤,他像一只归巢的信鸽似的作出响应。 3. I looking forward to your homing day and night. 我日夜盼望你归航。 4. A homing pigeon was sent forth to carry the message. 一只信鸽被放出去递送消息。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shrewd', '[ʃruːd]', 'adj.精明的；敏锐的；狡猾的', '1. Her brother is a shrewd businessman. 她兄弟是个精明的生意人。 2. It was a shrewd assessment and probably pretty close to the truth. 这个评估很有道理，可能相当正确。 3. He\'s an artist, a scientist and a shrewd businessman (all) rolled into one. 他既是艺术家，又是科学家，同时还是个精明的生意人。 4. His skill in negotiating earned him a reputation as a shrewd tactician. 他的谈判技巧使他赢得了精明战略家的名声。', '副词: shrewdly 比较级: shrewder 最高级: shrewdest');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indent', '[ɪn\'dent]', 'n.订货单 n.凹痕 v.切割成锯齿状；缩排；定货', '1. On the adjoining page we hand you an indent for various line, which please ship at once. 我们已将委托购买的各种商品在附页列明，请立即发运。 2. A firm order is often called an indent. 确定的订单常称作订货单。 3. The fallen tree limb left a big indent on his car. 掉下来的树枝在他的车上留下了一个大凹口。 4. The mountains indent the horizon. 山峦使地平线成锯齿状。', '过去式: indented 过去分词: indented 现在分词: indenting 第三人称单数: indents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('metallic', '[mə\'tælɪk]', 'adj.金属的；金属般的', '1. This is a kind of metallic paint. 这是一种有金属光泽的涂料。 2. The emery is a hard metallic substance. 金刚砂是非常坚硬的金属物质。 3. I heard metallic sounds when I was studying. 在我学习的时候我听到了金属撞击的声音。 4. He spoke in a thin, metallic voice. 他用尖细的金属般的声音说话。', '副词: metallically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('choose', '[tʃuːz]', 'v.选择；决定', '1. It\'s up to you to choose where we should go. 我们要去的地点,由你负责选择。 2. He will choose banking as his career. 他将选择银行业做为职业。 3. He chose not to go home until later. 他决定晚一点才回家。', '名词: chooser 过去式: chose 过去分词: chosen 现在分词: choosing 第三人称单数: chooses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('neutralize', '[\'nuːtrəlaɪz]', 'v.使中立；使无效；中和', '1. Switzerland was neutralized in 1815. 瑞士于一八一五年实现中立。 2. High taxes will neutralize increased wages. 高税收将抵销增加了的工资。 3. Nothing could neutralize its good effects. 没有什么能抵消它所产生的好影响。 4. Lime was used to neutralize the acidity of the soil. 曾用石灰来中和土壤中的酸性。', '名词: neutralizer 过去式: neutralized 过去分词: neutralized 现在分词: neutralizing 第三人称单数: neutralizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('notate', '[\'noʊteɪt]', 'vt. 把 ... 写成标志', '1. No knowledge of notate, chord names, keys etc. are required. 1. no知识notate ，共鸣的姓名，按键等是必需的。 2. Space Beacons - Allows you to leave messages in sectors, some people use them to notate danger etc. 太空烽燧-让你在区域内留言,其他人可用来传递危险讯息等。 3. Instead, treat the mistakes that you find as if you were the reviewer; notate them and track them together with all the other review comments. 您应当将自己当作审阅者来处理错误;对这些错误作上标记,然后将它们与所有其他检查评论一起进行跟踪。 4. to notate a piece of music 把一段音乐用乐谱记下', '过去式: notated 过去分词: notated 现在分词: notating 第三人称单数: notates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cabin', '[\'kæbɪn]', 'n.船舱；机舱；小木屋 vt.抑制 vi.住在小屋', '1. He made out of the cabin on hearing the siren. 他一听到汽笛声就立即走出船舱。 2. Fine. Can you let me have a cabin for two? 好的，能给我订一间二人船舱吗? 3. My cabin is on E deck. 我的舱位在E层甲板。 4. Cabin light will be dim for takeoff. 机舱灯将会因飞机起飞而变暗。 5. The criminal was cabined all the day. 这个犯人整天受到限制。 6. The old man cabined in the forest. 这位老人住在森林的小屋里。', '过去式: cabined 过去分词: cabined 现在分词: cabining 第三人称单数: cabins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mercy', '[\'mɜːrsi]', 'n.仁慈；怜悯；恩惠；宽恕', '1. Mercy to the enemies means cruelty to the people. 对敌人的仁慈就意味着对人民的残忍。 2. They showed their enemies no mercy. 他们不给敌人半点仁慈。 3. They never appealed to us for mercy. 他们从不向我们乞求怜悯。 4. The commander showed mercy to the prisoners of war. 司令官对战俘十分怜悯。', '名词复数: mercies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shovel', '[\'ʃʌvl]', 'n.铲；挖斗机；一铲的量 vt.铲；铲成；舀 vi.用铲子', '1. A shovel was leaning against the wall. 一把铁铲靠墙放着。 2. He seized a shovel and went into the garden. 他抓起一把铁铲走进花园这。 3. The giant shovel is biting off big chunks from the hill. 巨型铲土机正在把小山头一大口一大口地啃掉。 4. He put a shovel of coal on to the fire. 他往火炉里加了一铲煤。 5. Shovel the snow away from the garden path. 把花园小径上的积雪铲掉。 6. I believe you have forgotten how to shovel right. 我想你忘记了怎样正确地用铲子了。', '过去式: shoveled/shovelled 过去分词: shoveled/shovelled 现在分词: shoveling/shovelling 第三人称单数: shovels/shovels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stew', '[stuː]', 'n.炖汤；焖；烦恼 v.炖汤；焖；忧虑', '1. Today I spent the whole afternoon making oxtail stew. 今天我花了整整一个下午去炖牛尾汤。 2. She is all in a stew over her lost trunk. 她因丢失衣箱而十分烦恼。 3. Today I spent the whole afternoon stewing oxtail. 今天我花了整整一个下午去做焖牛尾。', '形容词: stewy 过去式: stewed 过去分词: stewed 现在分词: stewing 第三人称单数: stews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wrath', '[ræθ]', 'n.愤怒；激怒', '1. The mother allayed her son\'s wrath. 母亲平息了他儿子的愤怒。 2. Envy and wrath shorten the life. 嫉妒和愤怒会缩短生命。 3. A gentle answer turns away wrath, but a harsh word stirs up anger. 和善的回答能驱散愤怒,但是粗鲁的话语却能激起怒火。 4. The wrath of the people is now aroused. 人们被激怒了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evident', '[\'evɪdənt]', 'adj.明白的；明显的', '1. Now it became evident that he spoke two languages at once. 现在我才明白，原来他心里一套表面一套。 2. Inertia is evident in our every day experiences. 惯性在我们日常生活中是很常见的。 3. The purpose may not be immediately evident. 这种目的不一定显而易见。 4. The rationale for the present study is evident. 该研究的理论基础是明显的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('demonstrate', '[\'demənstreɪt]', 'vt.证明；演示；示范 vi.示威', '1. How can you demonstrate to us that your story is true? 你怎样才能向我们证明你所说的属实呢? 2. Realized benefits demonstrate good practice. 已实现的利益证明好的实践。 3. You have to demonstrate how to operate the computer. 你得演示一下如何使用这台计算机。 4. The students are demonstrating a chemical law in the laboratory. 学生们正在实验室里演示一条化学定理。 5. The workers marched through the streets with flags and banners to demonstrate against the rising cost of living . 工人们在街上游行，手执旗帜示威抗议生活费用的高涨。', '过去式: demonstrated 过去分词: demonstrated 现在分词: demonstrating 第三人称单数: demonstrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('Saturn', '[\'sætɜːrn]', 'n.土星 n.[罗神]农神', '1. Saturn is the planet sixth in order from the sun. 土星是依次离太阳的第六颗行星。 2. The huge Saturn rocket would send men to the moon. 巨大的土星式运载火箭将把他们送往月球。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nutriment', '[\'njuːtrəmənt]', 'n.营养品；促进生长的东西', '1. Effects of nutriment on lipid metabolism. 脂质代谢无明显异常。 2. Please took the medicine dawn nutriment. 吃过饭后请吃药. 3. The nutriment price ITe ought to be pretty high. 这儿的食品价格确定很高。 4. Are you employ to the nutriment ITe? 你习惯吃这儿的饭菜吗？', '形容词: nutrimental');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beverage', '[\'bevərɪdʒ]', 'n.饮料', '1. What beverage would you like? 你想喝什么饮料？ 2. The bar steward is accountable to the beverage manager. 酒吧间服务员要对餐饮部经理负责。 3. He never drinks alcoholic beverage. 他从不喝含酒精的饮料。 4. The beverage is often colored with caramel. 这种饮料常用焦糖染色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clog', '[klɑːɡ]', 'vt.阻塞；妨碍 vi.阻塞；结块；跳木屐舞 n.木屐；障碍', '1. Heavy traffic clogged the freeways. 拥挤的交通堵塞了高速公路 2. Don\'t rinse the leaves out into the sink: you\'ll clog the drain. 不要将叶子冲洗掉进污水槽，会堵塞阴沟的。 3. Sludge can also clog oil passages and prevent normal engine lubrication. 油泥还会阻塞油路，妨碍发动机的正常润滑工作。 4. The pipes are clogging up. 管子渐渐被堵塞。', '过去式: clogged 过去分词: clogged 现在分词: clogging 第三人称单数: clogs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abundant', '[ə\'bʌndənt]', 'adj.丰富的；充裕的', '1. Indonesia is abundant in petroleum deposits. 印尼的石油蕴藏量丰富。 2. The agricultural commodities are abundant this year. 今年的农产品很丰富。 3. Birds concentrate in places where food is abundant. 鸟聚集在食物丰盛的地方。 4. There is abundant firewood in the forest. 森林里有充裕的薪柴可用。', '副词: abundantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instance', '[\'ɪnstəns]', 'n.例子；场合；情况；要求；诉讼程序 vt.举例说明', '1. This is only one instance out of many. 这不过是许多例子中的一个。 2. Can you quote a recent instance? 你能举出一个最近的例证吗? 3. You may get along well with your boss but there will always be that specific instance where you want to say more than you should. 也许你和你老板相处得很好，但总是会有一些特殊的场合，你想说的话多于你应该说的。 4. In most instances the pain soon goes away. 在多数情况下,这种疼痛很快就会消失。 5. The game was exciting, as was instanced by the score. 依分数所示, 这场比赛是很紧张的。', '过去式: instanced 过去分词: instanced 现在分词: instancing 第三人称单数: instances');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defer', '[dɪ\'fɜːr]', 'v.推迟；延期；使延期入伍 v.顺从；把…委托给他人', '1. They cannot defer their departure any longer. 他们再不能推迟动身了。 2. We wish to defer our decision until next week. 我们希望推迟到下星期再作出决定。 3. I will defer going till I have more money. 我要延期到我有更多钱时才去。 4. The company agree to defer payment for three month. 公司同意延期三个月后付款。 5. We should defer to our parents\' wishes. 我们应当顺从父母的意愿。', '形容词: deferrable 名词: deferrer 过去式: deferred 过去分词: deferred 现在分词: deferring 第三人称单数: defers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fatuous', '[\'fætʃuəs]', 'adj.愚昧的；发呆的；愚笨的', '1. He seems take pride to make such fatuous remarks. 他好像对自己愚蠢的讲话还洋洋自得。 2. Television commercials seem more smug and fatuous than ever. 电视的广告似乎比以前更沾沾自喜和愚蠢。', '副词: fatuously 名词: fatuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disposition', '[ˌdɪspə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.性情；倾向；安排；处置；控制；[计算机] 配置情况', '1. She has a calm and introverted disposition. 她性格文静内向。 2. Joanna had a gentle retiring disposition. 乔安娜性格温柔而腼腆。 3. The child had a placid disposition. 这个孩子性情温和。 4. They showed a disposition to sign the contract. 他们表示有签订合同的意愿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deceitful', '[dɪ\'siːtfl]', 'adj.欺诈的；欺骗的', '1. It is hard to get on with a deceitful man. 与一个好欺诈的人很难和睦相处。 2. The backsliding was undemocratic and deceitful. 这种倒施逆行既违反了民主,又欺骗了人民。 3. No one can trust a deceitful person. 没有人会相信爱骗人的人。', '副词: deceitfully 名词: deceitfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indignant', '[ɪn\'dɪɡnənt]', 'adj.愤慨的；愤愤不平的', '1. People are indignant by their shooting of innocent civilians. 对于他们枪杀无辜平民，人们感到义愤填膺。 2. He is indignant at the false accusation. 他对被诬告愤愤不平。', '副词: indignantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elaborate', '[ɪ\'læbəreɪt]', 'adj.详尽的；复杂的；精心的；精美的 v.详细地说明；用心制作；推敲；变得复杂', '1. He launched into an elaborate explanation of his theory. 他开始详尽地阐发他的理论。 2. Her elaborate hairstyle, to her disappointment, just amused us. 令她失望的是,她复杂的发型只让我们感到好笑。 3. It was not the old man to indulge in elaborate preliminaries. 这位老人向来不做那种煞费苦心的开场白。 4. She had prepared herself for a very elaborate show. 她准备了一场非常精美的表演。 5. She went on to elaborate her argument. 她进而详尽阐述了她的论点。', '副词: elaborately 名词: elaborateness 过去式: elaborated 过去分词: elaborated 现在分词: elaborating 第三人称单数: elaborates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('synchronize', '[\'sɪŋkrənaɪz]', 'vt.使同步；使同时发生 vi.同时发生', '1. We synchronized our watches. 我们校准了我们的手表。 2. He synchronized the time bomb with his watch. 他用自己的手表时间校正了计时炸弹的时间。 3. All of the branches of the firm should be synchronized and cooperated. 公司各部门应该协调合作。 4. The wheels must synchronize as they revolve. 这些轮子须同速转动。', '名词: synchronization 过去式: synchronized 过去分词: synchronized 现在分词: synchronizing 第三人称单数: synchronizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acrimonious', '[ˌækrɪ\'moʊniəs]', 'adj.尖刻的；激烈的；刻薄的；辛辣的', '1. His tendency to utter acrimonious remarks alienated his audience. 他发表尖刻言论的倾向使得他的听众疏远了他。 2. His parents went through an acrimonious divorce. 他的父母在激烈争吵中离了婚。', '副词: acrimoniously 名词: acrimoniousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distribute', '[dɪ\'strɪbjuːt]', 'v.分配；散发；分布', '1. Please distribute books among the students. 把书发给学生。 2. Clothes and blankets have been distributed among the refugees. 向难民分发了衣服和毯子。 3. We distribute handbills on the street every weekend. 我们每周都要在街上散发传单。 4. Some types of plants are widely distributed. 有些植物分布得很广。', '过去式: distributed 过去分词: distributed 现在分词: distributing 第三人称单数: distributes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('uncanny', '[ʌn\'kæni]', 'adj.神秘的；不可思议的', '1. The silence was uncanny. 静得出奇。 2. I had an uncanny feeling of being watched. 我有一种奇怪的感觉，好像有人监视我。 3. His powers of observation were uncanny. 他的观察能力非常惊人。 4. The similarity between the two is uncanny. 这两者之间有着不可思议的相似性。', '副词: uncannily 比较级: uncannier 最高级: uncanniest 名词: uncanniness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compulsive', '[kəm\'pʌlsɪv]', 'adj.极有趣的；强迫的；上瘾的；难以抑制的', '1. Their story makes compulsive reading. 他们的故事读起来有趣极了。 2. She went through periods of compulsive overeating. 她经历了强迫性暴食的几个阶段。 3. What are your most compulsive habits? 你最强迫性的习惯是什么？ 4. There exist many groups designed to help compulsive gamblers. 有许多组织有计划的帮助那些上瘾的赌徒克服陋习。', '副词: compulsively 名词: compulsiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chapel', '[\'tʃæpl]', 'n.小礼拜堂；礼拜仪式；唱诗班；印刷厂工会；殡仪馆', '1. The chapel was dedicated in 1880. 这座小教堂于1880年举行献堂礼。 2. He built a chapel as a shrine to the memory of his dead wife. 他建了一座小教堂作为悼念亡妻的圣所。 3. The frescos in the Sistine Chapel are world-famous. 西斯廷教堂的壁画举世闻名。 4. The ghost of Lady Margaret is supposed to haunt this chapel. 据说玛格丽特女士的鬼魂常在这个礼拜堂出没。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acting', '[\'æktɪŋ]', 'n.演戏；演技；假装 adj.代理的；临时的；供演出用的 动词act的现在分词.', '1. Acting is his bread and butter. 演戏就是他的饭碗。 2. Despite fine acting by several well-known stars, it was a young newcomer who stole the show. 尽管几位名角演出都很出色,却未曾想竟让一名新秀抢尽风头。 3. He is famous for his fine acting. 他以演技精湛著称。 4. Harry decided to humor Fred by acting like he was grossed out by the toffee. 哈利假装吃太妃糖时呕吐，以此让弗雷高兴一下。 5. The acting chairman did everything appropriately. 代理主席把每件事都做得恰如其分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('roe', '[roʊ]', 'n.鱼卵；鱼子；獐鹿', '1. Salmon roe is marketed as analogous to caviar. 鲑鱼卵被作为鱼子酱的类似产品推向市场。 2. We will serve smoked cod\'s roe at the dinner. 宴会上我们将上一道熏鳕鱼子。 3. Such guards also protect against fraying by roe deer. 这种保护措施还可防止獐鹿摩擦损伤。', '名词复数: roe');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diligent', '[\'dɪlɪdʒənt]', 'adj.勤奋的；用功的', '1. The diligent student gets up before dawn every day. 这个勤奋的学生每天天亮以前就起床了。 2. Their students are diligent about their studies. 他们的学生勤奋学习。 3. She is more diligent than any other students in her class. 她是班上最用功的学生。', '副词: diligently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('epitomize', '[ɪ\'pɪtəmaɪz]', 'v. 摘要； 概括； 成为 ... 的缩影； 作为典范', '1. For a practice that has come to epitomize unethical business behavior, insider trading has received surprisingly little ethical analysis. 现实中，内幕交易已经成为不道德商业行为的缩影，但奇怪的是，几乎没人对其进行过伦理分析。 2. The Summer Season could be said to epitomize all that is traditionally English about England. 英格兰夏日是传统英格兰的缩影，要想定义它，的确是件难事。', '过去式: epitomized 过去分词: epitomized 现在分词: epitomizing 第三人称单数: epitomizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interject', '[ˌɪntər\'dʒekt]', 'v.插话；突然插入', '1. If I may interject a note of caution into the discussion ... 请容我在讨论中插句话，要注意 ... 2. When I brought up the question of funding, he quickly interjected that it had been settled. 我刚提出筹集基金的问题，他急忙插嘴说问题已经解决了。', '形容词: interjectory 名词: interjector 过去式: interjected 过去分词: interjected 现在分词: interjecting 第三人称单数: interjects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jeopardy', '[\'dʒepərdi]', 'n.危险', '1. For a moment his life was in jeopardy. 他的生命一度陷入危险中。 2. The security of this entire universe is in jeopardy! 整个宇宙安全都处在危险当中。', '名词复数: jeopardies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tissue', '[\'tɪʃuː]', 'n.纸巾；薄绢；(生物的)组织；织物', '1. She gave us a box of tissues. 她递给我们一盒纸巾。 2. She wiped off the sweat from her face with a piece of facial tissue. 她用一张面巾纸擦掉脸上的汗水。 3. On her head was a tiny cap of silver tissue. 她头上戴着一顶银丝小帽。 4. Human tissue is made up of cells. 人体的组织是由细胞构成的。', '形容词: tissuey');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impetuous', '[ɪm\'petʃuəs]', 'adj.冲动的；猛烈的；轻率的', '1. He is an impetuous young man. 他是个易冲动的年轻人。 2. She regretted her impetuous decision. 她后悔自己做了冲动的决定。 3. It was impetuous of her to do that. 她竟做那种事,真是鲁莽。 4. Youngsters are usually more impetuous than old people. 年轻人常比老年人急躁。', '副词: impetuously 名词: impetuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trying', '[\'traɪɪŋ]', 'adj.难受的；令人厌烦的 动词try的现在分词.', '1. It had been a most trying experience for them. 那对他们来说是一段十分难受的经历。 2. Your son is turning out to be very trying. 你的儿子变得非常惹人烦。', '副词: tryingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('torment', '[\'tɔːrment]', 'n.苦痛；拷问；折磨；烦恼 vt.使苦恼；折磨', '1. He was in torment after the operation. 手术后他非常痛苦。 2. That child is a torment to his parents. 这孩子对他的父母是一种折磨。 3. He suffered a hideous torment when the enemy caught him. 敌人抓到他后，他受到可怕的折磨。 4. What a little torment that child is! 这孩子真烦人！ 5. She torments everyone with silly questions. 她用无聊的问题来烦扰大家。', '副词: tormentingly 过去式: tormented 过去分词: tormented 现在分词: tormenting 第三人称单数: torments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fossil', '[\'fɑːsl]', 'n.化石；食古不化的人；守旧的事物', '1. Coal is a fossil fuel. 煤是一种矿物燃料。 2. This fossil may be over 2 million years old. 这化石可能超过二百万年了。 3. He found a piece of fossil of an ancient bird. 他发现一块古代鸟类的化石。 4. Professor Baboon is not an old fossil. 巴布恩教授不是落伍的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('superficial', '[ˌsuːpər\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.表面的；肤浅的', '1. Superficial scratches can be easily removed. 表面的划痕很容易擦掉。 2. A superficial injury is not serious. 表面的伤不太严重。 3. This is only superficial prosperity. 这只是表面繁荣。 4. He is too superficial to appreciate great literature like this. 他太肤浅，无法欣赏这类文学巨著。', '副词: superficially 名词: superficiality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('efficient', '[ɪ\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.效率高的；胜任的', '1. This is a highly efficient new heating system. 这是个高效的新取暖系统。 2. Consequently, we have been developing a more efficient engine. 结果,我们已经开发了一台更高性能的发动机。 3. The success of CAD systems is becoming more dependent on the efficient drafting. cad系统的成功在很大程度上取决于草图的制图效率。 4. He\'s efficient at his job. 他胜任工作。', '副词: efficiently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aquatic', '[ə\'kwætɪk]', 'adj.水生的；水中的；水上的 n.水生动物；水草', '1. Many land animals evolved from aquatic creatures. 许多陆地动物是从水生生物演化而来的。 2. Aquatic food chains are different from terrestrial ones. 水生食物链不同于陆地食物链。 3. The oil leakage from the cargo ship caused severe aquatic pollution. 货船的漏油造成严重的海域污染。 4. Swimming and water skiing are both aquatic sports. 游泳和滑水都是两项水上运动。 5. Everybody knew that the aquarium is the raising aquatic animal\'s place. 大家知道水族馆是饲养水生动物的地方。', '副词: aquatically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embody', '[ɪm\'bɑːdi]', 'vt.使具体化；包含；代表，体现；使(精神)肉体化', '1. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 2. He embodies a new idea in his paintings. 他在画中体现思想。 3. The latest computer model embodies many new features. 最新型的计算机具备许多新功能。 4. The new car embodies many improvements. 这辆新车包含了许多改进的项目。', '过去式: embodied 过去分词: embodied 现在分词: embodying 第三人称单数: embodies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mollify', '[\'mɑːlɪfaɪ]', 'v.安慰；安抚；平息', '1. He tried to find ways of mollifying her. 他想方设法安慰她。 2. Regulators often force government-backed firms to shrink to mollify rivals. 监管者常迫使政府支持的公司收缩经营以安抚其竞争对手。 3. She managed to mollify her angry boss. 她顺利平息了她生气的老板。 4. He tried to mollify his father\'s anger by apologizing. 他企图以认错来减缓他父亲的怒气。', '形容词: mollifiable 副词: mollifyingly 名词: mollification 过去式: mollified 过去分词: mollified 现在分词: mollifying 第三人称单数: mollifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('augment', '[ɔːɡ\'ment]', 'vt.增加 n.增加；补充物', '1. They hit upon another idea to augment their income. 他们又想出一个增加收入的办法。 2. Hotel workers depend on tips to augment their usually small salaries. 饭店的工作人员主要靠小费来增加他平时微薄的收入。 3. He augments his income by teaching in the evenings. 他晚上去教书以增加收入。 4. They hit upon another idea to augment their income. 他们又想出一个增加收入的办法。', '形容词: augmentable 名词: augmenter 过去式: augmented 过去分词: augmented 现在分词: augmenting 第三人称单数: augments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('patron', '[\'peɪtrən]', 'n.赞助人；老主顾；守护神', '1. Modern artists have difficulty in finding patrons. 现代艺术家们很难找到赞助人。 2. He inscribed those poems to his patron. 他将这些诗献给他的赞助人。 3. This store has many patrons. 这家商店有许多老顾客。 4. The usher handed the patron to a reserved seat. 引座员把顾客引到预订的座位上', '形容词: patronal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sour', '[\'saʊər]', 'adj.酸的；酸腐的；刻薄的 v.变酸', '1. Most green fruit is sour. 大多数未熟的水果都是酸的。 2. The dish\'s gone sour. 这菜已经变质了。 3. He\'s always got a sour look on his face, and he has never said anything friendly. 他总是板着脸,从来不说一句好听的话。 4. The hot weather has soured the milk. 炎热的天气使牛奶变酸了。', '形容词: sourish 副词: sourly 比较级: sourer 最高级: sourest 名词: sourness 过去式: soured 过去分词: soured 现在分词: souring 第三人称单数: sours');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hamper', '[\'hæmpər]', 'vt.妨碍；阻止 n.大篮子', '1. Our progress was hampered by the bad weather. 我们前进时受到了恶劣天气的阻碍。 2. Outdated conventions and bad customs hamper the growth of production. 陈规陋习妨碍生产的发展。 3. The heavy rain hampers the flow of traffic. 大雨阻碍了交通运行。 4. There are some apples in a picnic hamper. 在野餐用的大篮子里有许多苹果。', '过去式: hampered 过去分词: hampered 现在分词: hampering 第三人称单数: hampers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('charisma', '[kə\'rɪzmə]', 'n.非凡的领导力；魅力', '1. The President has great personal charisma. 总统具有超凡的个人魅力。 2. Most movie stars have a lot of charisma. 大部分电影明星很有魅力。', '名词复数: charismata');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aggression', '[ə\'ɡreʃn]', 'n.进攻；侵犯；侵害；侵略', '1. For a dog,an erect tail indicates aggression. 对狗而言，竖立起来的尾巴表示进攻。 2. Aggression gives us a great deal of suffering for our own mind. 这种进攻性的心态给我们的心灵带来了非常大的痛苦。 3. Retaliation only escalates a bully\'s aggression. 报复只会助长欺凌者的侵犯气焰。 4. You should learn what to do in case of an act of aggression. 你应该学习如何应对侵犯行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('operator', '[\'ɑːpəreɪtər]', 'n.操作员；技工；管理者；报务员；【计】运算符', '1. I am a computer operator. 我是一名计算机操作人员。 2. Is this man a teaccher or an operator? 这个男人是老师还是名操作员? 3. The lathe is being adjusted by the operator. 这台车床正由技工在调准。 4. My father is a private operator in civil aviation. 我父亲是私营民航的管理者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refresh', '[rɪ\'freʃ]', 'v.（使）恢复精神；提神；提醒', '1. A cool drink refreshed me after my long walk. 走了很长的一段路之后，一杯冷饮使我恢复了精神。 2. He has drunk one cup of coffee to refresh oneself. 他喝了一杯咖啡提神。 3. I refreshed myself with a cup of coffee. 我喝了一杯咖啡给自己提提神。 4. Let me refresh your memory with some fact. 我来提几件事帮你恢复记忆吧。', '过去式: refreshed 过去分词: refreshed 现在分词: refreshing 第三人称单数: refreshes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tug', '[tʌɡ]', 'n.用力拉；拖船 v.用力拉', '1. Tom felt a tug at his sleeve. 汤姆觉得有人拉了拉他的衣袖。 2. Tom gave his sister\'s hair a hard tug. 汤姆使劲地扯了一下他姐姐的头发。 3. We had a great tug to persuade him. 我们费了很大的精力去劝服他。 4. The tug will lead the liner into the harbor. 拖船将把那艘客轮引入港口。 5. She tried to tug my hand away. 她试图把我的手拉开。', '名词: tugger 过去式: tugged 过去分词: tugged 现在分词: tugging 第三人称单数: tugs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brass', '[bræs]', 'n.黄铜(制品)；铜管（乐器）；厚脸皮 adj.黄铜的', '1. Brass is formed by the fusion of copper and zinc. 黄铜是由铜和锌熔合制成的。 2. The brass is too loud. 铜管乐器的声音太响了。 3. He walked in, bold as brass, and asked me to lend him 50! 他走进来，厚颜无耻地要我借给他50英镑！ 4. How do you have the brass to say that? 你怎么有脸那么说呢？ 5. The dwarf sat down and the elf rang the little brass bell. 侏儒坐下来，而小仙人摇了那小铜铃。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('carnage', '[\'kɑːrnɪdʒ]', 'n.大屠杀；残杀', '1. The battlefield was a scene of utter carnage. 战场完全是一片大屠杀的惨象。 2. Refugees crossed the border to escape the carnage in their homeland. 难民越过边界逃避国内的大屠杀。 3. Imagine the carnage if they ever escaped their cages. 想象一下它们一旦逃出铁笼后会出现的残杀景象！ 4. The ancient Rome battlefield was a scene of great carnage. 古罗马战场曾尸横遍地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('noted', '[\'noʊtɪd]', 'adj.著名的；有声望的 动词note的过去式和过去分词形式', '1. He is a noted authority on English literature. 他是著名的英国文学权威。 2. The garden has a lake copied from a noted one in China called Xihu. 公园里有一个湖是仿照中国著名的西湖建造的。', '副词: notedly 名词: notedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('motive', '[\'moʊtɪv]', 'n.动机；目的；主题 adj.发动的；运动的；动机的 vt.促使', '1. Her prime motive was personal ambition. 她的主要动机是为了实现个人的志向。 2. I don\'t understand what his motive is. 我不知道他的动机是什么。 3. The police have excluded robbery as a motive for the murder. 警方已排除该谋杀案中有抢劫的动机。 4. Can we assign jealousy as the motive for the crime? 我们能否确定这一犯罪动机是出于嫉妒? 5. The water provides the motive power that turns the mill wheel. 水提供了转动轮子的动力。 6. According to the order,Communist Jiang San motived the mass to fight against the Japanese army.they eradicated the enemy,and killed his brother Jiang Er,who was a traitor. 共产党员蒋三奉命加家乡发动群众开展武装斗争，最后消灭了当地日伪军，除掉汉奸，其兄蒋二。', '过去式: motived 过去分词: motived 现在分词: motiving 第三人称单数: motives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('command', '[kə\'mænd]', 'n.命令；指挥；掌握；[计算机] DOS命令 : 引用辅助命令处理器 v.命令；指挥；掌握；博得', '1. He growled a command to her to stop. 他咆哮着命令她停下来。 2. The company commander roared his command. 连长高声发布命令。 3. He has a hundred men under his command. 他指挥一百个人。 4. The army is under the king\'s direct command. 军队由国王直接统率。 5. The general commanded his men to attack the city. 将军下令部下攻城。', '过去式: commanded 过去分词: commanded 现在分词: commanding 第三人称单数: commands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unconventional', '[ˌʌnkən\'venʃənl]', 'adj.非传统的；不合惯例的；非常规的', '1. He was by nature revolutionary and unconventional. 他生来具有叛逆的、非传统的性格。 2. His was an unconventional path to parenthood, to say the least. 至少可以这样说，他不是传统意义上的父亲。 3. We need an unconventional approach to the problem. 我们需要一个打破惯例的处理问题的方法。 4. You seem to me to have nothing unconventional at all about you. 我可觉得你一点也没有违反习俗的地方。', '副词: unconventionally 名词: unconventionality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ore', '[ɔːr]', 'n.矿石；矿', '1. We will make an assay of the ore that he brought. 我们将对他带来的矿石做实验鉴定。 2. The ore is smelted in this large factory. 这个大型工厂里熔炼矿石。 3. This is an area rich in ore. 这里是个矿产丰富的地区。 4. But few of them had actually dug up any ore. 然而他们中只有少数几个确实挖了矿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('string', '[strɪŋ]', 'n.线；弦；一串；字串 vt.串起；收紧；悬挂；系；扎；抽去筋；使紧张；使兴奋 vi.连成一串', '1. Puppets are worked by strings. 木偶是用线来操纵的。 2. The E string of the violin needs screwing up. 这只小提琴的E弦需要调紧些。 3. We have had a string of complaints about the program. 我们已经收到了对该节目的一连串投诉。 4. If the logon fails, an empty string is returned. 如果登录失败,则返回空字符串。 5. She strung the beads with a fine nylon. 她用细尼龙线把珠子串了起来。', '过去式: strung 过去分词: strung 现在分词: stringing 第三人称单数: strings');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('empower', '[ɪm\'paʊər]', 'vt.授权；使能够', '1. The lawyer was empowered to pay all her bills. 律师已被授权偿付她的一切帐单。 2. The new laws empower the police to stop anybody in the street. 新法令授予警察可以在街上截停任何人的权利。 3. The new laws empower the police to search private house. 新的法律使警察得以搜查私人住宅。 4. Modern science and technology empower human beings to control natural forces more effectively. 现代科学技术使人类能更有效地制服自然。', '名词: empowerment 过去式: empowered 过去分词: empowered 现在分词: empowering 第三人称单数: empowers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('simply', '[\'sɪmpli]', 'adv.简单地；仅仅；简直', '1. Most of these problems won\'t simply dissolve. 大多数这些问题不会简单地解决。 2. Put simply, we accept their offer or go bankrupt. 简单地说吧，我们要么接受他们的条件，要么破产。 3. You may open the tin simply by pulling the puller. 你只要拉这个拉出器，就可以很容易地把罐头打开。 4. Is success simply a matter of working hard? 是否只要勤奋就能成功？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('muscle', '[\'mʌsl]', 'n.肌肉 v.硬挤；变硬实', '1. He strained his muscle in the match. 他在那次比赛中拉伤了肌肉。 2. The contraction of muscle is a reaction of the body. 肌肉的收缩是人体的一种反应。 3. He tried to muscle into the club. 他企图强行加入那个俱乐部。 4. Our competitors have been trying to muscle in for some years . 几年来，我们的竞争对手一直试图夺取利益。', '形容词: muscly 过去式: muscled 过去分词: muscled 现在分词: muscling 第三人称单数: muscles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interlude', '[\'ɪntərluːd]', 'n.中间；中间时间；插曲；介在中间的事件', '1. There will now be a 15-minute interlude. 现在有15分钟的中间休息。 2. Apart from a brief interlude of peace, the war lasted nine years. 除了一段短暂的和平，那场战争持续了九年。 3. Her time in Paris was a happy interlude in a difficult career. 她在巴黎期间是她艰辛的事业中一段愉快的插曲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('approve', '[ə\'pruːv]', 'v.批准；赞成；同意；称许', '1. The city council approved the building plan. 市议会批准了这项建筑计划。 2. I presume you will approve of the plan. 我相信你会赞成这个计划。 3. You can join the class if your parents approve. 如果你父母同意，你可以参加这个班。 4. I approve of your trying to earn some money, but please don\'t neglect your studies. 我同意你去挣一些钱，可是请不要误了功课。', '形容词: approvable 副词: approvingly 过去式: approved 过去分词: approved 现在分词: approving 第三人称单数: approves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hazardous', '[\'hæzərdəs]', 'adj.危险的；冒险的；碰运气的', '1. Everybody said that it was a hazardous investment. 大家都说那是一次危险的投资。 2. Dry-cleaners deal with many hazardous chemicals. 干洗工要跟很多危险的化学品打交道。 3. Nothing rewarded the hazardous experiment. 这个冒险的举动没有引起任何反应。 4. In this area arable farming is a hazardous practice. 在这个地区，可耕种的作物完全是碰运气的。', '副词: hazardously 名词: hazardousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recipient', '[rɪ\'sɪpiənt]', 'n.接受者；收信人', '1. China is now the world\'s sixth-largest trading partner and the second-largest recipient of foreign investment after the United States. 中国现在是世界第6大贸易国，仅次于美国的世界第二大外国投资接受国。 2. The recipients of prizes had their names printed in the paper. 获奖者名单登在报上。 3. The postman spent almost a whole day looking for the recipient of the letter. 邮递员几乎花了整整一天时间寻找该信的收信人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grumble', '[\'ɡrʌmbl]', 'v.发牢骚；抱怨；轰鸣 n.怨言；牢骚；轰隆声', '1. A lot of students grumble about heavy reading assignments. 许多学生发牢骚说阅读量太大。 2. It\'s not like him to grumble at her. 抱怨她可不像他的做法。 3. We\'ve got nothing to grumble about. 我们没什么可抱怨的。 4. They will grumble about having to do the work. 他们将为不得不干那项工作而抱怨。 5. I don\'t want to hear another grumble from you. 我不愿再听到你的怨言了。', '形容词: grumbly 副词: grumblingly 名词: grumbler 过去式: grumbled 过去分词: grumbled 现在分词: grumbling 第三人称单数: grumbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('section', '[\'sekʃn]', 'n.部分；部门；章节；区域；断面；剖面图；零件；路段；切开 v.划分；切开', '1. White lines divide the playing area into sections. 这些白线把赛区分成各个部分。 2. I hope someone competent will join our section. 我希望有能力的人加入本部门。 3. The report has a section on accidents at work. 报告中有一段谈到工作中的事故问题。 4. She lives near the business section. 她住在商业区附近。', '过去式: sectioned 过去分词: sectioned 现在分词: sectioning 第三人称单数: sections');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allocation', '[ˌælə\'keɪʃn]', 'n.分配；配置；安置', '1. They said the allocation of seats was unfair. 他们说席位的分配不公平。 2. Profits allocation is affected by many factors. 摘要影响利益分配的因素是很多的。 3. Asset allocation is the key to achieving your goals. 资产配置是实现你的目标的关键。 4. The companies merged to optimize the allocation of resources. 为了优化资源配置，这几家公司并产了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rim', '[rɪm]', 'n.边；框 vt.镶边 vi.形成边缘', '1. The water was even with the rim of the basin. 盆里的水与盆边平齐了。 2. She put a flower on the rim of the hat. 她在帽子边上放了一朵花。 3. She opened the door, and the yellow light from inside rimmed about her. 她打开门，里面射出的灯光在她的身影四周镶了一圈黄色的边。 4. The ball hit the rim and bounced off. 球击中篮框边缘并弹开了。 5. Trees rimmed the pool. 池塘边长了一圈树。 6. She opened the door, and the yellow light from inside rimmed about her. 她打开门，里面射出的灯光在她的身影四周镶了一圈黄色的边。', '过去式: rimmed 过去分词: rimmed 现在分词: rimming 第三人称单数: rims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fussy', '[\'fʌsi]', 'adj.过分装饰的；谨慎的；挑剔的；唠叨的，抱怨的', '1. I don\'t want anything too fussy. 我不要过分装饰的。 2. The little girl dislikes her fussy parents. 小女孩讨厌她那过分操心的父母。 3. She developed a peremptory and fussy disposition. 她养成了一种蛮横和过分注意细节的性格。 4. He is very fussy about his food. 他对于食物非常挑剔。', '副词: fussily 比较级: fussier 最高级: fussiest 名词: fussiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expeditious', '[ˌekspə\'dɪʃəs]', 'adj.〈正式或文〉迅速而有效率的；迅速完成的', '1. Sent the package by the most expeditious means. 以最快速有效的方式送包裹', '副词: expeditiously 名词: expeditiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('germinate', '[\'dʒɜːrmɪneɪt]', 'v.发芽；开始生长', '1. The cabbage germinated within a week. 白菜一星期内就发芽了。 2. Warmth is needed for the seeds to germinate. 种子发芽需要适当的温度。 3. An idea for a novel began to germinate in her mind. 一部小说的构思已经在她的头脑中萌发。 4. I saw everything about me surge forth and germinate. 我看见我周围的万物汹涌向前，欣欣向荣。', '形容词: germinative 名词: germination 过去式: germinated 过去分词: germinated 现在分词: germinating 第三人称单数: germinates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crush', '[krʌʃ]', 'v.压碎；击败；使...失望；折皱；压榨 n.压碎；压榨；极度拥挤；<口>迷恋', '1. A windmill is used to crush grain into flour. 风车被用来把谷粒轧成面粉。 2. It took him only 50 minutes to crush his opponent. 他只用了50分钟时间就击败了对手。 3. This victory inspired vigor in the Armenian national team and they finally crushed the English team. 这场胜利激起了亚美尼亚队的斗志,他们最终击败了英国队。 4. I was crushed that I wasn\'t invited. 没有受到邀请,我感到很失望。 5. I\'ve got a crush on my pretty toy pistol. 我非常喜欢我漂亮的玩具手枪。', '形容词: crushable 名词: crusher 过去式: crushed 过去分词: crushed 现在分词: crushing 第三人称单数: crushes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prolific', '[prə\'lɪfɪk]', 'adj.多产的；作品丰富的', '1. Shakespeare was a prolific writer. 莎士比亚是一个多产的作家。 2. Trollope\'s strict work routine enabled him to keep his day job as a civil servant while being such a prolific writer. 特罗洛普严格的工作常规使他成为一名如此多产的作家同时仍能让他白天做好公务员这份差使。', '副词: prolifically 名词: prolificacy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('harvest', '[\'hɑːrvɪst]', 'n.收成；收获；收割；成果；后果 v.收获；收割', '1. It happened that the harvest was bad in 1988. 碰巧一九八八年的收成很糟。 2. The fine summer harvest was not easily come by. 夏季的好收成不是容易得来的。 3. The harvest has been safely gathered in. 庄稼已妥善收获完毕。 4. We are all very busy because it\'s the harvest time. 因为现在是收获期，所以我们都非常忙。 5. Farmers harvest their crops in fall. 农民秋天收获庄稼。', '形容词: harvestable 名词: harvestability 过去式: harvested 过去分词: harvested 现在分词: harvesting 第三人称单数: harvests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('endeavor', '[ɪn\'devər]', 'n.尽力；努力 v.尽力；努力；力图', '1. Please make every endeavor to be early. 请尽量早点儿。 2. He failed in convincing the buyer despite endeavor. 尽管他已经尽力了,还是无法说服买主。 3. Where there is no hope, there can be no endeavor. 哪里没有希望,哪里就不可能有努力。 4. His success came from endeavor rather than opportunity. 他的成功与其说是由于机遇 5. The man endeavored to please his beloved wife. 那人尽量使他深爱的妻子快乐。', '名词: endeavorer 过去式: endeavored 过去分词: endeavored 现在分词: endeavoring 第三人称单数: endeavors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shun', '[ʃʌn]', 'v.避开；回避；避免', '1. His friends shunned him. 他的朋友都避开他。 2. They shun personal fame and gains. 他们不计个人名利。 3. This recluse shunned all company. 这位隐士不与任何人来往。 4. Wise men love truth, whereas fools shun it. 智者热爱真理,愚者回避真理。', '名词: shunner 过去式: shunned 过去分词: shunned 现在分词: shunning 第三人称单数: shuns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amass', '[ə\'mæs]', 'v.积聚；收集', '1. A speculator may try to amass great wealth. 投机商会想方设法积聚钱财。 2. Mr. Smith\'s business was very successful, and he was able to amass a fortune. 史密斯先生的事业极为成功，所以他积聚了一大笔财富。 3. She continues to amass a staggering amount of material on the history and technology relating to current-day mind control and other forms of abuse. 她继续收集在历史和技术上涉及到当今的精神控制和其他的孽待形式的令人惊愕的材料。 4. So, as you begin to amass this knowledge and these abilities, there will be others attracted to you for their own reasons because of what they can access through you. 所以，如同你们开始收集这知识和这些能力，将会有吸引他们自己的动机，因为他们能够通过你们访问。', '形容词: amassable 名词: amasser 过去式: amassed 过去分词: amassed 现在分词: amassing 第三人称单数: amasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transmit', '[træns\'mɪt]', 'vt.传达；传染；传送；代代相传 vi.(以无线电或有线电的方式)发送信号', '1. Gypsies frequently transmit recipes orally within the family. 吉普赛人经常以口头形式把秘方世代相传。 2. Please transmit my best regards to your lovely wife. 请转达我向您娇妻的致意。 3. This infection is transmitted by mosquitoes. 这种传染病是由蚊子传染的。 4. The tension soon transmitted itself to all the members of the crowd. 这种紧张情绪很快感染了人群中所有的人。', '形容词: transmittable 过去式: transmitted 过去分词: transmitted 现在分词: transmitting 第三人称单数: transmits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('minimize', '[\'mɪnɪmaɪz]', 'v.将 ... 减到最少；贬低', '1. Governments consider it prudent to minimize the risk. 各国政府均认为把这种危害降低到最小程度的做法是明智的。 2. The polar explorers took every precaution to minimize the dangers of their trip. 极地探险者十分小心谨慎，以便使旅途的危险性减少到最小。 3. A sound approach to the problem is to minimize the number of parts. 正确解决这一问题的方法是把零件的数目减至最少。 4. He minimized the value of her contribution to his research so that he got all the praise. 他极力贬低她在那项研究中的贡献，从而独获全部奖励。', '名词: minimization 过去式: minimized 过去分词: minimized 现在分词: minimizing 第三人称单数: minimizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vigilant', '[\'vɪdʒɪlənt]', 'adj.警戒的；警惕的', '1. We must keep an vigilant eye upon imperialism. 我们必须对帝国主义保持警戒。 2. A pilot must be vigilant at all times. 飞行员必须随时保持警惕。 3. The night shift has to be doubly vigilant. 值夜班要加倍警惕。 4. The British Prime Minister Gordon Brown has urged people to be vigilant against the potential terrorist attack. 英国首相戈登.', '副词: vigilantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tentacle', '[\'tentəkl]', 'n.(动物)触角；触须', '1. Each tentacle has 5,000 stinging cells and enough toxin to kill 60 humans. 每根触须都有5000个带刺的细胞，上面的毒液足以杀死60个人。', '形容词: tentacular');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coddle', '[\'kɑːdl]', 'v.娇养；溺爱；用文火煮', '1. He\'ll need to be coddled after his illness. 他病后需要悉心照料。 2. I would not coddle the child. 我不愿意溺爱这个孩子。 3. He never go to coddle his superior. 他从不去讨好上司。', '名词: coddler 过去式: coddled 过去分词: coddled 现在分词: coddling 第三人称单数: coddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('head', '[hed]', 'n.头部；头脑；顶端；领袖；硬币的正面 v.前进；为首；朝向 adj.首要的；前面的', '1. Please raise your head and look at the blackboard. 请抬起头来，看黑板。 2. The stone caught him on the side of the head. 那块石头击中他头部的侧面。 3. He had no head for business. 他毫无商业头脑。 4. We walked straight to the head of the line. 我们一直朝线路的顶端前进。 5. We are heading home. 我们正向家的方向走去。 6. My mother is the head librarian of the school library. 我的妈妈是学校图书馆管理员组长。', '过去式: headed 过去分词: headed 现在分词: heading 第三人称单数: heads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reckless', '[\'rekləs]', 'adj.鲁莽的；不计后果的；大意的', '1. He\'s a reckless driver. 他是个鲁莽的司机。 2. He apologized for their reckless behavior. 他对他们的鲁莽行为道了歉。 3. His brother is a reckless gambler. 他的弟弟是个不计后果的赌徒。 4. It\'s the way you try to sound rough or reckless. 你说起话来故意这样显得很粗野或者毫不在乎。', '副词: recklessly 名词: recklessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flaw', '[flɔː]', 'n.瑕疵；缺陷；破绽；裂缝 v.使破裂；有瑕疵', '1. Unfortunately, I found that your work had a tiny flaw. 很不幸 2. The flaw in this vase makes it less valuable. 这个花瓶因为有点缺陷，不那么值钱了。 3. I can\'t find a flaw in his argument. 在他的论点中,我找不到任何破绽。 4. Your argument has a fatal flaw. 你的论点有一个致命的错误。 5. The jealous colleague decided to flaw the project plans. 这名嫉妒的同事决定给这些项目计划搞破坏。', '形容词: flawy 过去式: flawed 过去分词: flawed 现在分词: flawing 第三人称单数: flaws');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concession', '[kən\'seʃn]', 'n.让步；特许权；租界；妥协', '1. I hope you can make some concession. 我希望你能做些让步。 2. I must make a concession to him. 我必须对他让步。 3. They interpreted her silence as concession. 他们把她的沈默解释为让步。 4. He has an ice-cream concession in the subway station. 他在地铁站拥有一家冰淇淋分店。', '形容词: concessional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('container', '[kən\'teɪnər]', 'n.容器；集装箱', '1. A reactor is a container for chemical reaction. 反应器是进行化学反应的容器。 2. The volume of this container is 2 cubic meters. 这个容器的容量是两立方米。 3. The goods are packed in airtight container. 货物被装在密封的集装箱内。 4. You need to empty the container. 你必须腾空这个集装箱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disintegrate', '[dɪs\'ɪntɪɡreɪt]', 'vi.瓦解；崩溃 vt.使粉碎；使碎裂', '1. The alliance will soon disintegrate unless something is done to pull it together. 这个联盟会很快瓦解，除非采取措施加强它的团结。 2. Their marriage rapidly disintegrated. 他们的婚姻迅速破裂了。 3. The family is starting to disintegrate. 这个家庭要破裂了。 4. The plane flew into a mountain and disintegrated on impact. 飞机冲向一座山，撞得粉碎。', '形容词: disintegrative 名词: disintegrator 过去式: disintegrated 过去分词: disintegrated 现在分词: disintegrating 第三人称单数: disintegrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oceanographer', '[ˌəʊʃə\'nɒɡrəfə(r)]', 'n.海洋学家', '1. His son, also a distinguished oceanographer, tells us in a recent book how intensely his father enjoyed every new experience, every new discovery concerning the world about him. 他的儿子，也是一位杰出的海洋学家，在最近出版的新书中告诉我们他的父亲多麽强烈地享受每一个新的经验，每一个关于周遭世界的新发现。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dauntless', '[\'dɔːntləs]', 'adj.无畏的；勇敢的；不屈不挠的', '1. Those man are certainly possessed of dauntless courage. 那些都是天不怕地不怕的硬汉子。 2. The author characterized the leading character in the novel as a dauntless hero. 作者将小说中的主人公描绘成一个大无畏的英雄。 3. They are all dauntless soliders. 他们都是勇敢的士兵。 4. Dauntless in spirit,they became steeled through hardship. 他们不屈不挠,在艰苦的生活中锻炼得更加坚强了。', '副词: dauntlessly 名词: dauntlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ban', '[bæn]', 'v.禁止；剥夺权利 n.禁令；禁止', '1. The government has banned the use of chemical weapons. 政府已经禁止使用化学武器。 2. She was banned from athletics for two years after failing a drug test. 她在药检中被查出服用禁用药物而被禁赛两年。 3. A ban on the importation of drugs has been issued recently. 最近已经发布了禁止进口毒品的法令。 4. There is a ban on smoking in the theatre. 这剧院内禁止吸烟。', '名词复数: bani 过去式: banned 过去分词: banned 现在分词: banning 第三人称单数: bans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('facet', '[\'fæsɪt]', 'n.小平面；方面；刻面', '1. They beat us in every facet of the game. 他们在比赛的每个小层面都打败了我们。 2. He has perfected himself in every facet of his job. 他已使自己对工作的各个方面都得心应手。 3. Locomotion is merely one facet of action. 移动只是行动的一个方面而已。 4. Being a well-paid business woman is only one facet of her life. 高薪阶层职业妇女的身份只是她生活的一个方面。', '形容词: faceted');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dull', '[dʌl]', 'adj.呆滞的；钝的；迟钝的；无趣的；暗的 v.变钝；迟钝', '1. Jack had all work but no play, making him a dull boy. 杰克只学不玩,这使得他成为一个呆笨的孩子。 2. It\'s impossible to cut a pineapple with such a dull knife. 用一把这么钝的刀子切菠萝是不可能的。 3. The mind becomes dull if the body doesn\'t get on exercise. 要是身体得不到锻炼,头脑也会迟钝的。 4. This book is rather dull. 这本书很枯燥。 5. The heating was turned up high to dull his audience\'s senses. 暖气温度被调到很高，以至于听众的意识变得迟钝。', '形容词: dullish 副词: dully 比较级: duller 最高级: dullest 名词: dullness 过去式: dulled 过去分词: dulled 现在分词: dulling 第三人称单数: dulls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('catalyst', '[\'kætəlɪst]', 'n.催化剂；刺激因素', '1. War is a catalyst to help them to choose. 战争是一副催化剂来帮助他们选择。 2. Debate is the best catalyst of thought. 争论是思想最好的催化剂。 3. This tragedy will be a catalyst for good. 这场悲剧会是美好的催化剂。 4. The results were then used to make better car catalyst. 这一研究的成果可随后用于生产出效果更好的汽车催化剂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advisable', '[əd\'vaɪzəbl]', 'adj.明智的；可取的', '1. It is advisable to be forearmed. 预作准备是明智的。 2. This line of conduct seems advisable to me. 这一行动方针对我来说似乎是很可取的。 3. It is not advisable just to work away without making a timely summing-up of experience. 一味埋头干下去不做及时的经验总结是不可取的。', '副词: advisably 名词: advisability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('optimistic', '[ˌɑːptɪ\'mɪstɪk]', 'adj.乐观的；乐观主义的', '1. The book ended on an optimistic note. 该书的结尾寓意乐观。 2. The stockholders are optimistic about the company\'s future. 股东对公司的前景很乐观。 3. We are still optimistic, whatever the result (may be). 我们仍然乐观，不论结果如何。 4. I was exhausted and relieved, but I wasn\'t wildly optimistic. 我已感到精疲力尽,同时也感到如释重负,然而,我并不抱盲目乐观的态度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('classic', '[\'klæsɪk]', 'n.杰作；古典作品；第一流艺术家 adj.最优秀的；传统的；古典的', '1. \"War and Peace\" is a literary classic. 《战争与和平》是一部经典文学著作。 2. The idea of a classic is historically bound up with the view. 从历史上来看，古典的想法和这个观点有着密切的联系。 3. This is a really classic French champagne. 这确实是上等的法国香槟酒。 4. The novel is regarded as one of the classic works. 这篇小说被公认为是最优秀的作品之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strait', '[streɪt]', 'n.海峡；困境 adj.困难的；窘迫的；<古>狭窄的；严格的', '1. We will transit the strait at night. 我们将在夜间通过那个海峡。 2. We passed through the Strait of Magellan. 我们穿过了麦哲伦海峡。 3. I hear you are in poor financial straits. 我听说你处于经济困难之中。 4. The door is rather strait. 这门相当窄。', '副词: straitly 名词: straitness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('penury', '[\'penjəri]', 'n.贫穷；拮据', '1. Laid-off workers fall into penury. 下岗职工陷入贫困。 2. He was cradled in the lap of penury . 他自幼生活在贫困的环境里。 3. Hardship and penury wore him out before his time. 受穷受苦使他未老先衰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('generous', '[\'dʒenərəs]', 'adj.慷慨的；宽宏大量的；丰厚的；丰盛的；味浓的', '1. She was always very generous in her charity. 她行善时总是很慷慨。 2. Such generous actions stamp him as a man of honour. 他的这些慷慨行为表明他是个君子。 3. I regret having been so generous to that scoundrel. 我后悔不该对那坏家伙如此宽宏大量。 4. I am doubly indebted to you-- for the party and for your generous gift! 你为我操办欢送会并赠送厚礼,这样的深情厚谊我铭记在心。', '副词: generously 名词: generousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equipment', '[ɪ\'kwɪpmənt]', 'n.设备；装备；器材', '1. The government has an interest in importing scientific equipment. 政府对引进科学设备非常感兴趣。 2. We should make a better use of the existing equipment. 我们应该更好地利用现有设备。 3. The equipment must be bought from a supplier approved by the company. 设备必须从公司认可的供应商那里购买。 4. The Army is auctioning off a lot of old equipment. 军队正在把大量旧装备拍卖掉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sustain', '[sə\'steɪn]', 'vt.支持；承受；维持；认可；经受', '1. His hope for future sustained him. 对未来的希望支持了他。 2. The ice will not sustain your weight. 这冰承受不了你的体重。 3. Some species may not be able to sustain the pressure from such prevalent raids. 一些物种无法承受这种猖撅的偷猎行为带来的压力。 4. They had sufficient food to sustain life. 他们有足够维持生命的食物。', '形容词: sustainable 名词: sustainability 过去式: sustained 过去分词: sustained 现在分词: sustaining 第三人称单数: sustains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fair', '[fer]', 'adj.公平的；晴朗的；美丽的; 相当的；（皮肤、毛发等）浅色的；白皙的 n.展览会；市集 adv.公平地，直接地', '1. He won the game fair and square. 他赢得这次比赛是公平的。 2. Soames said that he was not getting a fair go. 索米斯说他没有得到公平的对待。 3. The rainbow promises fair weather. 虹预示晴朗的天气。 4. A foul morning may turn to a fair day. 天气不好的早晨能变成晴朗的白天。 5. The visitors spied the exhibits at the fair. 参观者细细察看展览会上的陈列品。', '比较级: fairer 最高级: fairest 名词: fairness 过去式: faired 过去分词: faired 现在分词: fairing 第三人称单数: fairs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glamorous', '[\'ɡlæmərəs]', 'adj.富有魅力的；迷人的', '1. The long red carpet was laid out for this glamorous occasion. 为了这个富有魅力的时刻，地上铺了长长的红地毯。 2. Do not be swayed by glamorous advertisements. 不要为富有迷惑力的广告所左右。 3. The glamorous actress always went shopping with many attendants crowding round her. 那位富有魅力的女演员逛街时总是被前呼后拥地围着。 4. My job is not a very glamorous one but it does have its moments. 我的工作虽不算十分吸引人，但也自有其乐趣所在。', '副词: glamorously 名词: glamorousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('creek', '[kriːk]', 'n.小湾；小溪 Creek. n.克里克族；克里克人；克里克语', '1. It will be absolutely necessary that the place you may select have a small harbor, creek, or bay, into which my corvette can enter and remain at anchor. 你挑选的地方务必要有一个小港，小溪或小湾，可以让我的帆船进去抛锚。 2. There are often wild ducks swimming in the creek. 小溪中常有野鸭戏水。 3. Eddie\'s going to lure Courtney down to Muddy Creek. 艾迪去把卡特妮引诱下来使小溪污浊。 4. The area was originally occupied by the native Creek and Cherokee Indians who had lived in the region for centuries. 几世纪以来，这里原先是当地印第安克里克族和切罗基族的居住地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('selfish', '[\'selfɪʃ]', 'adj.自私的；利己的', '1. A selfish person always thinks about himself. 一个自私的人总是想着自己。 2. I am becoming more and more irritated by his selfish behaviour. 我对他那种自私的行为愈加恼火起来。 3. I call his behaviour mean and selfish. 我认为他的行为卑鄙、 自私。 4. Nobody but you could be so selfish. 除了你之外，谁也不会这样自私。', '副词: selfishly 名词: selfishness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('govern', '[\'ɡʌvərn]', 'v.统治；支配；管理；规定；控制', '1. Education makes a people easy to lead, but difficult to drive: easy to govern but impossible to slave. 教育让一个民族容易被领导，却很难被驱使；容易被统治，却很难被奴役。 2. You must not be governed by the opinions of others. 你决不要受别人意见的支配。 3. Such laws also govern the chances of commodity production and exchange. 这种规律也支配着商品生产和商品交换的偶然性： 4. Riches either serve or govern the possessor 财富可以侍候主人,也可以支配主人', '形容词: governable 过去式: governed 过去分词: governed 现在分词: governing 第三人称单数: governs 名词: governance');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('regenerate', '[rɪ\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'vt.再生 adj.再生的；复原的 n.重生者；再生器官', '1. Their aim is to regenerate British industry. 他们的目的是复兴英国的工业。 2. The party soon regenerated under her leadership. 该党在她的领导下很快焕然一新。 3. But I was regenerate with a strong will and faith of sure success in my heart! 但是我却内心带者坚强的意志和必胜的信念再次重生！ 4. This is a regenerate society. 这是个观念更新的社会。', '形容词: regenerable 副词: regenerately 名词: regenerator 过去式: regenerated 过去分词: regenerated 现在分词: regenerating 第三人称单数: regenerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decorate', '[\'dekəreɪt]', 'v.装饰；布置；装修；授予某人奖章或其他奖状', '1. We decorated the house for Christmas. 我们装饰房屋过圣诞节。 2. My mother likes to decorate rooms. 我妈妈非常喜欢装饰房间。 3. I\'ll bring some balloons to decorate. 我要带些气球去装饰装饰。 4. May I help you decorate the room? 我可以帮你装饰布置房间吗？', '过去式: decorated 过去分词: decorated 现在分词: decorating 第三人称单数: decorates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('linguistics', '[lɪŋ\'ɡwɪstɪks]', 'n.语言学', '1. He is engaged in studies in linguistics. 他从事于语言学的研究。 2. Literary studies have been cross-fertilized by new ideas in linguistics. 文学研究从语言学方面的新见解中受益良多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disreputable', '[dɪs\'repjətəbl]', 'adj.声名狼藉的；见不得人的；不体面的', '1. That dive attracts every disreputable people. 那家下流酒吧吸引声名狼藉的人。 2. Francs have a rich and disreputable past. 法郎历史悠久，声名狼藉。 3. I\'ve been accused of using disreputable methods to get what I want. 我被指控采取不正当的手段以谋取私利。 4. He had a vaguely disreputable appearance. 他看上去有些不那么体面。', '副词: disreputably 名词: disreputability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('domain', '[doʊ\'meɪn]', 'n.领地；领域；范围', '1. Each of her cousins had charge of his own domain. 她的每一个亲属主管着自己的领地。 2. The kitchen is my wife\'s domain, and she doesn\'t like me going into it. 厨房是我妻子的领地,她不愿让我进去。 3. As soon as you create an account for the user, the user can participate in a secure domain. 一旦您为用户创建了一个帐号，用户就可以进入安全域中。 4. The doctor works in the domain of public health. 医生在公众健康范围内工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('violently', '[\'vaɪələntli]', 'adv.猛烈地；强烈地；暴力地', '1. His face began to work violently. 他的脸部开始剧烈的抽搐。 2. She had never thought he\'d blow up so violently. 她从来没有想到他会生这样大的气。 3. They are violently opposed to the idea. 他们强烈反对这个想法。 4. His views were violently stormed by journalistic circles. 他的观点受到新闻界的强烈抨击。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confide', '[kən\'faɪd]', 'v.吐露；委托；信赖', '1. She confided to me the secret. 她向我吐露了那个秘密。 2. Nowadays girls seldom confide in their mothers. 现在的女孩很少对母亲吐露心事。 3. Can I confide my children to your care? 托你照顾一下我的孩子好吗? 4. Don\'t confide in him. 不要信赖他。', '名词: confider 过去式: confided 过去分词: confided 现在分词: confiding 第三人称单数: confides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stroll', '[stroʊl]', 'n.闲逛；漫步 v.闲逛；漫步', '1. She decided to take a stroll in the garden. 她决定在花园散步。 2. A stroll round the garden hardly qualifies as exercise! 在花园转转算不上锻炼！ 3. My father sometimes goes out for a stroll with a stick in his hand. 父亲有时候带着手杖出去散步。 4. A casual stroll through a lunatic asylum shows that faith does not prove anything. 疯人院的一次闲庭漫步说明信念并不能证明一切。 5. We stroll through a meadow full of tall grass. 我们漫步走过长满高草的牧场。', '过去式: strolled 过去分词: strolled 现在分词: strolling 第三人称单数: strolls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('petrify', '[\'petrɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使石化；使发呆 vi.石化', '1. To convert to a mineral substance;petrify. 使成矿使转化为矿物质；使石化 2. To convert to a mineral substance; petrify. 使成矿使转化为矿物质；使石化 3. Redundant slogans are apt to petrify a man\'s thinking. 口号过多容易使人思想僵化。 4. A mutation of a gateway decoration. Uses Petrify attacks. 由凯旋门上的装饰品变化而来。使用可造成石化的攻击。', '过去式: petrified 过去分词: petrified 现在分词: petrifying 第三人称单数: petrifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avoid', '[ə\'vɔɪd]', 'vt.避免；逃避；[律]使无效；撤销', '1. You should avoid unnecessary repetition. 你应避免不必要的重复。 2. They all avoided mentioning that name. 他们都避免提及那名字。 3. He\'ll grab at any excuse to avoid doing the dishes. 他会随便找个借口来逃避洗碗。 4. No one can avoid his own responsibility. 没有人能够逃避自己的责任。', '形容词: avoidable 副词: avoidably 名词: avoider 过去式: avoided 过去分词: avoided 现在分词: avoiding 第三人称单数: avoids');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('testimony', '[\'testɪmoʊni]', 'n.证明；证据', '1. His hearty laughter is testimony of his happiness. 他尽情的欢笑可以证明他很幸福。 2. Nothing could refute her testimony that the driver was drunk. 她关于那个司机已经喝醉的证词无可辩驳。 3. The witness is giving false testimony. 那个证人在作伪证。 4. The statement is confirmed by testimony. 这个说法由证据所证实了。', '名词复数: testimonies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overhaul', '[\'oʊvərhɔːl]', 'vt.翻修；仔细检查；革新；赶上 n.彻底检查；全面检修', '1. You should overhaul your car engine. 你应检修你的汽车发动机。 2. The engines were overhauled completely before our departure. 在我们出发之前马达都彻底检修过。 3. There have already been several attempts to overhaul the system. 已有多次尝试彻底改革。 4. The fast cruiser soon overhauled the old cargo boat. 快速巡逻艇迅即赶上那艘旧货船。 5. I\'ve taken my typewriter in for an overhaul. 我已把打字机拿去彻底检修了。', '名词: overhauler 过去式: overhauled 过去分词: overhauled 现在分词: overhauling 第三人称单数: overhauls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accessible', '[ək\'sesəbl]', 'adj.可得到的；易接近的；可进入的；易受影响的；易理解的', '1. Such information is not really accessible. 这种信息不是很容易得到的。 2. A manager should be accessible to his staff. 一个管理人员应该让职员感到平易近人。 3. This database is only accessible by the authorized manager. 只有授权的管理员才可以访问此数据库。 4. He is not accessible to pity. 他不大有同情心。', '副词: accessibly 名词: accessibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('furnace', '[\'fɜːrnɪs]', 'n.炉子；熔炉；闷热地带；严峻考验', '1. This room is like a furnace. 这屋子热得象火炉一样。 2. Would you please fire the furnace? 你去给炉子添加燃料好吗? 3. The metal glowed in the furnace. 金属在熔炉里发出灼热的光。 4. He endured the furnace of his friends\'blame after the accident. 事故发生之后,他遭朋友指责的考验', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deter', '[dɪ\'tɜːr]', 'vt.阻止；威慑；威吓', '1. No difficulty can deter us from trying it again. 没有困难可以阻止我们再试一次。 2. The extreme cold deterred him from going out. 极度寒冷使他打消外出的念头。 3. It\'s this edge that gives newclear weapons their power to deter. 正是这个优势赋予了核武器威慑力量。 4. The fact that we have the big bombs will deter our enemies from attacking us 我们拥有这种重型炸弹的事实威慑住敌人不敢向我们进攻。', '形容词: deterrable 名词: determent 过去式: deterred 过去分词: deterred 现在分词: deterring 第三人称单数: deters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gene', '[dʒiːn]', 'n.基因', '1. The position that a given gene occupies on a chromosome. 基因座在一条染色体上某种给定基因所占的位置 2. The degree to which an expressed gene produces its effects in an organism. 基因的表现度描述一个组织中的一个基因产生作用的程度 3. In addition to gene, intelligence also depends on an adequate diet, a good education and a decent home environment. 除了遗传基因外，智力的高低还取决于良好的营养，良好的教育和良好的家庭环境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pitch', '[pɪtʃ]', 'n.球场；程度；音调；推销；投掷；街头商贩摊位；沥青；树脂；松脂 v.投；颠簸；搭帐篷；定调；推销；用沥青覆盖', '1. The pitch is too small to play football on. 球场太小了, 无法踢足球。 2. Speculation has reached such a pitch that a decision will have to be made immediately. 这种胡乱猜测甚嚣尘上，已经到了必须立即解决的程度了。 3. The pitch depends on the frequency. 音调的高低是由频率决定的。 4. He has a very clever sales pitch. 他推销商品的口才很好。 5. She pitched the ball as far as she could. 她尽力把球投得远一些。', '过去式: pitched 过去分词: pitched 现在分词: pitching 第三人称单数: pitches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assure', '[ə\'ʃʊr]', 'vt.使确信；使放心；确保', '1. Her success as an actress was now assured. 她当演员很成功，已毋庸置疑了。 2. They tried to assure him of their willingness to work. 他们尽力使他相信他们乐意工作。 3. I can assure you that your son will be happy here. 我可以向你保证，你儿子在这里会很快乐的。 4. They were assured that everything possible was being done. 已经向他们保证，凡是可能做的都做到了。', '形容词: assurable 名词: assurer 过去式: assured 过去分词: assured 现在分词: assuring 第三人称单数: assures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('general', '[\'dʒenrəl]', 'adj.普遍的；全面的；一般性的；大致的；笼统的；常规的；总的；首席的 n.将军；一般', '1. The announcement was met with general rejoicing. 该项宣布受到普遍的欢迎。 2. Her predictions are so general that they could apply to anybody. 她的预测很全面,放之四海而皆准。 3. As a general rule, prices follow demands. 一般而言,物价随需求而变化。 4. They gave a general description of the man. 他们对这个男人作了大致的描述。 5. The general is a respectable man. 那位将军是个令人肃然起敬的人物。', '名词: generalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commentator', '[\'kɑːmənteɪtər]', 'n.评论员；解说员；注释者', '1. As a hard-nosed commentator, I deplore it. 但作为一个讲究实际的评论员，我对此感到惋惜。 2. He is an informed commentator on political events. 他是一位消息灵通的政治评论员。 3. The commentator and the announcer are both for the giant. 解说员和播报员都偏爱巨人队。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opal', '[\'oʊpl]', 'n.欧泊；蛋白石', '1. Opals are milky gems. 蛋白石是乳白色的宝石。 2. It was a round opal, red and fiery, set in a circle of tiny rubies. 那是一块圆形蛋白石，红红的，象火焰一般，上面镶着一圈红宝石。', '形容词: opaline');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('magnesium', '[mæɡ\'niːziəm]', 'n.镁', '1. Magnesium is the nutrient element in plant growth. 镁是植物生长的营养要素。 2. Dr Green prescribed magnesium sulphate. 格林医生开的药是硫酸镁。', '简写符号: Mg');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('biochemistry', '[ˌbaɪoʊ\'kemɪstri]', 'n.生物化学', '1. Her research is breaking new ground in biochemistry. 她的研究正在开辟生物化学的新开地。 2. I am going to start my doctorate in biochemistry next year. 我准备明年开始攻读生物化学博士学位。', '形容词: biochemical 副词: biochemically 名词: biochemist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hazard', '[\'hæzərd]', 'n.危险；冒险；危害 vt.冒险；赌运气 阿扎尔（英超切尔西队球员）', '1. The car had its hazard warning lights on. 这辆汽车亮起了危险信号灯。 2. He had put his own life in hazard. 他是在拿自己的生命来冒险。 3. There are many serious health hazards associated with smoking. 许多危害健康的情况都与吸烟有关。 4. He hazarded all his money in the attempt to save the business. 他为挽救这家企业，不惜冒险投入他的全部金钱。', '过去式: hazarded 过去分词: hazarded 现在分词: hazarding 第三人称单数: hazards');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('malicious', '[mə\'lɪʃəs]', 'adj.怀恶意的；恶毒的', '1. He was bespattered by malicious gossip . 他遭到恶意的流言蜚语的诋毁。 2. This malicious and unprovoked attack astounded him. 这个恶意的无端攻击使他吃惊。 3. You ought to kick back at such malicious slander. 你应当反击这种恶毒的污蔑。 4. The girl\'s reputation was defiled by malicious gossips. 那位姑娘的名誉因为恶毒的流言蜚语而受损。', '副词: maliciously 名词: maliciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flask', '[flæsk]', 'n.细颈瓶；烧瓶；小水瓶', '1. A balloon is mysteriously \"sucked\" into a flask. 一个气球神秘地被吸进了一个细颈瓶。 2. Please carry a flask with you at all times during the hike. 在徒步旅行期间请随身携带一个长颈瓶。 3. The graduation is marked on the side of the flask. 烧瓶侧面有刻度标志。 4. A flask, conjured from thin air, was thrust into his shaking hand by Hermione. 赫敏将一个凭空变出来的烧瓶塞在了他颤抖着的手里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('benevolent', '[bə\'nevələnt]', 'adj.仁慈的；乐善好施的', '1. The original designers of the human body were benevolent beings. 人类身体的最初设计者是仁慈的生命体。 2. His benevolent nature prevented him from refusing any beggar who accosted him. 他生性仁慈的，对任何一个向他乞讨的乞丐都慷慨解囊。 3. But can some EU members continue to treat Russia as a benevolent ally? 但是，是否一些欧盟成员国仍可以把俄罗斯当作是一个乐善好施的盟友？ 4. A benevolent employer has a sincere interest in the welfare of his employees. 一个乐善好施的老板对于做好自己员工的福利待遇是真心实意的。', '副词: benevolently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('component', '[kəm\'poʊnənt]', 'n.零部件；元件；组成部分；成分 adj.组成的；构成的', '1. The factory supplies components for the car industry. 该工厂向汽车业供应零部件。 2. Each of the components is useful in its degree. 每一个元件都各有程度不同的用处。 3. The militia is a component of the state\'s armed forces. 民兵是国家武装力量的组成部分。 4. A chemist can seperate a medicine into its components. 化学家能把一种药物的各种成分分解出来。 5. Can you resolve it into its component elements? 你能把它分解为组成它的元素吗?', '形容词: componential');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rebate', '[\'riːbeɪt]', 'n.回扣 vt.减少；变钝 vi.减少', '1. He get a tax rebate at the end of the year. 他在年底得到了一笔退回的税款。 2. Buyers are offered a cash rebate. 购买者享受现金回扣。 3. Could you grant me a premium rebate? 你能给我保险费折扣吗? 4. How can you rebate your tax on your summer job? 你怎样才能减纳你夏季劳动所得税呢? 5. It goes against our principle to give rebate to our clients. 给客户回扣有悖于我方原则。', '名词: rebater 过去式: rebated 过去分词: rebated 现在分词: rebating 第三人称单数: rebates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mime', '[maɪm]', 'n.哑剧；丑角；模仿 vt.做哑剧表演；模仿 vi.演出哑剧角色', '1. They will perform a short mime later. 待会他们将表演一出短的哑剧。 2. I couldn\'t speak Chinese, but I showed in mime that I wanted a drink. 我不会讲汉语，但我作摹拟动作表示要一杯饮料。 3. He mimed the part of a drunken man. 他以哑剧形式表演醉汉。 4. Ask a child to come to the front and pick a card and mime the action. 叫一个学生到教室前边来，拿一张卡片并模仿卡片上要求的动作。', '名词: mimer 过去式: mimed 过去分词: mimed 现在分词: miming 第三人称单数: mimes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convey', '[kən\'veɪ]', 'vt.表达；传达；运输；转移', '1. I find it hard to convey my feelings in word. 我觉得难以用言语表达我的感情。 2. Word will suffice to convey his grief. 他的悲伤足以用言辞表达。 3. A vibrating membrane in the ear helps to convey sounds to the brain. 耳膜的振动帮助声音传送到大脑。 4. This train conveys both passengers and goods. 这趟列车客货均载。', '形容词: conveyable 过去式: conveyed 过去分词: conveyed 现在分词: conveying 第三人称单数: conveys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reason', '[\'riːzn]', 'n.原因；理由；理智；理性 v.理论；论证；推理；劝说', '1. That is the reason why I don\'t like it. 那就是我不喜欢它的原因。 2. He is able to explain the reason because he was present at that time. 他当时在场,所以他能解释原因。 3. We have reason to believe that he was murdered. 我们有理由相信他是被谋杀的。 4. We shall in no way let reason be defeated by impulse. 我们决不能让冲动战胜理智。 5. Who can reason with you when you are so stubborn? 你这么执拗的时候,谁能和你理论?', '名词: reasoner 过去式: reasoned 过去分词: reasoned 现在分词: reasoning 第三人称单数: reasons');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cautious', '[\'kɔːʃəs]', 'adj.谨慎的；十分小心的', '1. She is cautious of telling secrets. 她很谨慎，不会泄露秘密。 2. He is cautious in his choice of words. 他措辞很谨慎。 3. They\'ve taken a very cautious approach. 他们采取了十分谨慎的态度。 4. The old lady is very cautious with money. 那位老太太用钱很谨慎。', '副词: cautiously 名词: cautiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pilferage', '[\'pɪlfərɪdʒ]', 'n.偷窃', '1. Besides, cartons are easy to cut open, and this increases the risk of pilferage. 此外，纸箱很容易割开，这就增加了偷窃的风险。 2. In case of theft and pilferage, you may be assured that you will get indemnification from the insurance company concerned. 万一发生偷窃，你们可以放心，保险公司将会给予赔偿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bait', '[beɪt]', 'n.饵；引诱 v.以饵引诱；逗弄；中途休息', '1. The fish snapped at the bait. 那鱼一下子咬住了鱼饵。 2. Earth worms are often used as bait. 蚯蚓常用作鱼饵。 3. The steaming cake was a bait for the hungry boy. 那热气腾腾的蛋糕对这个饥饿的男孩是个诱惑。 4. As soon as I mentioned money he rose to the bait, and became really interested. 我一提钱他便怦然心动，上了我的钩。 5. They bait the mousetrap with stale cheese. 他们用变质的乳酪作捕鼠夹的诱饵。', '名词: baiter 过去式: baited 过去分词: baited 现在分词: baiting 第三人称单数: baits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defection', '[dɪ\'fekʃn]', 'n.背叛；脱党；离会', '1. His defection to the other side was the ultimate betrayal. 他变节投向另一方是最终的背叛。 2. In the game, cooperation and defection result in differing payoffs depending on what the other participants do. 在游戏中，合作和背叛所得到的后果将根据其他参与者的作为而定。 3. The defection of a large number of back-benchers brought down the last government. 大量的不居要职的普通议员脱党，造成前任政府的垮台。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avenue', '[\'ævənuː]', 'n.林荫道；大街；途径手段', '1. He stands on the corner of a wide avenue. 他站在宽阔的林荫道的角落里。 2. I meet him by chance on Fifth Avenue. 我偶然在第大街上遇到他。 3. The avenue was crowded with people. 大街上挤满了人。 4. Hard work is a sure avenue to success. 勤奋是可靠的成功之道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spouse', '[spaʊs]', 'n.配偶', '1. He never mentioned his spouse. 他从来不提自己的妻子。 2. They get free ticket for their spouse. 他们为家属领到了免费的票。 3. What is your spouse immigration status? 你配偶的移民身份是什么? 4. Your spouse\'s family are your -in-laws. 你配偶的家人是你的姻亲。', '过去式: spoused 过去分词: spoused 现在分词: spousing 第三人称单数: spouses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nimble', '[\'nɪmbl]', 'adj.敏捷的；伶俐的；机敏的', '1. He is a nimble climber. 他是个敏捷的登山者。 2. She knitted a pair of mittens for me with her nimble fingers. 她用灵巧的双手为我织了一副手套。 3. The nurse sewed up the wound with nimble fingers. 护士用灵巧的手指缝好了伤口。 4. Habits will make us have two nimble hands and a clumsy brain. 习惯会使我们的双手伶俐而头脑笨拙。', '副词: nimbly 比较级: nimbler 最高级: nimblest 名词: nimbleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contrive', '[kən\'traɪv]', 'v.图谋；发明；设计；设法做到', '1. The prisoner contrived a way to escape. 囚犯图谋越狱。 2. He contrived to gain their votes. 他施展计谋获得了他们的选票。 3. He contrived a new machine for flying. 他设计了一种新式飞行器。 4. Can you contrive to be at the station by noon? 你能设法在中午前赶到车站吗?', '名词: contriver 过去式: contrived 过去分词: contrived 现在分词: contriving 第三人称单数: contrives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nutrition', '[nu\'trɪʃn]', 'n.营养', '1. Variety is not a guarantee of good nutrition. 品种多并不能确保营养好。 2. This food provides all the nutrition your dog needs. 本食品含有狗所必须的一切营养。 3. A balanced diet provides nutrition for your body. 均衡的食物使你的身体获得营养。', '形容词: nutritional 副词: nutritionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prospective', '[prə\'spektɪv]', 'adj.预期的；未来的', '1. We receive prospective results in the experiment. 我们在实验中得到了预期的结果。 2. Tom is the prospective buyer of my house. 汤姆是可能购买我的房屋的人。 3. I hope you can give this your immediate attention so that I can notify the prospective guests promptly. 我希望您能对此予以迅速考虑，以便我能及时通知期待的客人。 4. She is married to a prospective lawyer. 她嫁给了一个未来的律师。', '副词: prospectively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grocery', '[\'ɡroʊsəri]', 'n.杂货店 adj.杂货的 （复）groceries：食品杂货.', '1. Her mother began to operate a small grocery. 她母亲开始经营一家小杂货店。 2. She summed up the bills from the grocery with great care. 她非常仔细地合计那些来自食品杂货店的帐单。 3. He\'s bound up with the grocery trade in some way or another. 他同食品杂货业有着某种密切的关系。 4. A new supermarket opened across the street, and Peter\'s grocery business was soon in a bad way. 街对面开了一家新的超级市场,这使彼得的杂货店的生意马上萧条下来。', '名词复数: groceries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('submissive', '[səb\'mɪsɪv]', 'adj.服从的；顺从的', '1. She followed him like a submissive child. 她对他百依百顺，像个听话的孩子。 2. The submissive daughter was never able to fight against her parents. 这个顺从的女儿从不和她的父母吵架。 3. He is a humble and submissive servant . 他是个恭顺的仆人。', '副词: submissively 名词: submissiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('champion', '[\'tʃæmpiən]', 'n.拥护者；冠军；优胜者；勇士 vt.拥护；保卫；为 ... 而斗争', '1. He is a champion of women\'s rights. 他是妇女权利的卫士. 2. He is the undisputed champion. 他是无可争辩的冠军。 3. He is a champion at writing familiar essays. 他是写小品文的好手。 4. Every absurdity have a champion to defend it. 任何谬论都拥有拥护它的斗士。 5. He is forced to champion unpopular causes. 他被迫去支持一些不得人心的事业。', '过去式: championed 过去分词: championed 现在分词: championing 第三人称单数: champions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('benefit', '[\'benɪfɪt]', 'n.利益；津贴；义演；保险金；借助 vt.有益于；得益', '1. It was for the benefit of your company that we did that. 我们这样做都是为了你们公司的利益。 2. Applications for unemployment benefits dropped last month. 上个月申请失业津贴的人数下降了。 3. A benefit performance will be held tonight. 今晚有义演。 4. The unemployed are entitled to receive other unemployment insurance benefits during the period of receiving unemployment insurance compensation. 失业人员在领取失业保险金期间,按照规定同时享受其他失业保险待遇。 5. The new hospital will benefit the entire community. 新医院将有益于整个社区。', '过去式: benefited/benefitted 过去分词: benefited/benefitted 现在分词: benefiting/benefitting 第三人称单数: benefits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('supreme', '[suː\'priːm]', 'adj.最高的；至上的；极度的', '1. The general was girded with the supreme power. 将军被授予最高权力。 2. The safety of the people is the supreme law. 人民的安全是最高的法律。 3. Supreme authority resides in the State. 最高权力属于国家。 4. Wisdom is the supreme part of happiness. 智慧是幸福的顶峰。', '副词: supremely 比较级: supremer 最高级: supremest 名词: supremeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evolve', '[i\'vɑːlv]', 'v.(使)逐步形成；(使)逐步演变；进化', '1. The American constitution was planned; the British constitution evolved. 美国宪法是精心制定的，英国宪法是约定俗成的。 2. He has evolved a new theory after many years of research. 他经过多年的研究，逐渐总结出了新的理论。 3. If women do not evolve, men definitely will change. 女人一成不变，男人一定会变。 4. Why did humans evolve to walk upright? 人类为何进化到了直立行走的姿态?', '形容词: evolvable 名词: evolvement 过去式: evolved 过去分词: evolved 现在分词: evolving 第三人称单数: evolves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ruthless', '[\'ruːθləs]', 'adj.残忍的；无情的', '1. The ruthless enemy killed the old lady. 残忍的敌人杀害了那位老太太。 2. To foreign observers, American capitalism looks ruthless. 对于外国人来说，美国的资本主义看起来是残忍的。 3. He\'s a ruthless businessman, as I know to my cost. 我吃了苦头后才知道他是个无情的商人。 4. Go up against ruthless street racers out to win at any cost. 不惜任何代价对赢上升对抗无情的街道叁赛者。', '副词: ruthlessly 名词: ruthlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conceal', '[kən\'siːl]', 'vt.隐藏；隐瞒；掩盖', '1. He concealed himself behind the tree. 他藏在树后。 2. It is against law to conceal evidence. 隐藏证据是违法的。 3. It is wrong for a man to conceal things from his wife. 一个男人对妻子隐瞒事情是不对的。 4. She tried to conceal what she had done to them. 她试图隐瞒对他们所做的事。', '形容词: concealable 名词: concealer 过去式: concealed 过去分词: concealed 现在分词: concealing 第三人称单数: conceals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flatter', '[\'flætər]', 'v.奉承；恭维；取悦；显得好看', '1. My boss likes it when we flatter him. 我的老板喜欢我们奉承他。 2. Friends who flatter you to your face are not true friends. 凡是当面奉承你的朋友不是真朋友。 3. He flattered her about her cooking. 他恭维她的烹调手艺。 4. It\'s impossible for you to ask a girl to teach you how to flatter another. 你不可能让一个女孩教你如何取悦另一个女孩。', '副词: flatteringly 名词: flatterer 过去式: flattered 过去分词: flattered 现在分词: flattering 第三人称单数: flatters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('edifice', '[\'edɪfɪs]', 'n.大厦；大建筑物；大型支柱', '1. This edifice is used as a working place. 这栋大厦是工作用的。 2. There is a huge Victorian edifice in the area. 该地区有一幢维多利亚式的庞大建筑物。 3. The legislature is housed in an impressive granite edifice. 立法机构位于一幢引人注目的花岗岩大楼里。 4. The whole edifice of his hopes was destroyed . 他心中的希望整个都毁了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('linear', '[\'lɪniər]', 'adj.直线的；长度的；线性的', '1. Students do not always progress in a linear fashion. 学生不会总是顺着一条直线进步。 2. The flow is linear, with some iterations in the planning phase. 过程流程是直线的，在计划阶段会有一些迭代。 3. He\'s making linear measurements. 他正在进行长度测量。 4. Not all types of motions are linear in character. 并非所有类型的运动在性质上都是线性的。', '副词: linearly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('participate', '[pɑːr\'tɪsɪpeɪt]', 'vi.参加；参与 vt.分享', '1. Everyone in the class is expected to participate in the discussion. 希望全班同学参加讨论。 2. In the ancient Greek Olympics, only men were allowed to participate in it. 在古希腊奥运会中,只允许男人参加比赛。 3. I don\'t want to participate in the English party. 我不想参加英语晚会。 4. Everyone in the class is expected to participate in the discussion. 希望全班同学参加讨论。 5. I participate your suffering and joy. 我和你同甘共苦。', '形容词: participative 名词: participation 过去式: participated 过去分词: participated 现在分词: participating 第三人称单数: participates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('autocrat', '[\'ɔːtəkræt]', 'n.独裁者', '1. The autocrat strove in vain to deal with the situation. 那个独裁者努力应付这个情况,却徒劳无功。 2. He was an accomplished politician and a crafty autocrat. 他是个杰出的政治家,也是个狡黠的独裁者。', '形容词: autocratic 副词: autocratically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incompatible', '[ˌɪnkəm\'pætəbl]', 'adj.不相容的；不能并存的；矛盾的', '1. Those two blood groups are incompatible. 那两种血型是不相容的。 2. Therefore, Kant\'s philosophy is incompatible with ecofeminism. 因此，康德哲学与生态女性主义是不相容的。 3. These people think that communism and the Three People\'s Principles are incompatible. 他们以为共产主义和三民主义是不能并存的。 4. That is not incompatible with humility. 而这与谦卑是不矛盾的。', '副词: incompatibly 名词: incompatibleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('junction', '[\'dʒʌŋkʃn]', 'n.连接；会合处；交叉点', '1. The junction was not connected properly. 接口没有正确连接。 2. They decided to effect a junction of two armies. 他们决定两军会师。 3. The map is in error regarding the junction. 这张地图在这个交点上是绘制错了。 4. The gas station is at the junction of two highways 这个加油站位于两条公路的会合处。', '形容词: junctional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fiction', '[\'fɪkʃn]', 'n.小说；虚构；杜撰', '1. Real life is sometimes stranger than fiction. 现实生活有时比小说还离奇。 2. I like to read science fiction. 我喜欢读科幻小说。 3. It\'s important to distinguish fact from fiction. 把现实与虚构区分开来是很重要的。 4. His testimony is a complete fiction. 他的证言全是虚构。', '形容词: fictional 副词: fictionally 名词: fictionality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('charcoal', '[\'tʃɑːrkoʊl]', 'n.木炭；炭笔', '1. I threw a stick of charcoal in the fire. 我往火里扔了一根木炭。 2. We are well set up with charcoal for the winter. 我们准备好足够的木炭过冬。 3. He sketched the contours of a building with a charcoal pencil. 他用炭笔在纸上勾勒出了一个建筑物的轮廓。 4. I have been drawing since school days, using charcoal and carbon pencils. 上学的时候我就开始用炭笔和铅笔画画了。', '过去式: charcoaled 过去分词: charcoaled 现在分词: charcoaling 第三人称单数: charcoals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('receiver', '[rɪ\'siːvər]', 'n.听筒；接收器；收款员；接受者；破产管理官', '1. Please put the receiver back after calling. 打完电话后，请把听筒放回原位。 2. He jammed the receiver down on the cradle. 他把听筒猛力往支架上放下。 3. The television receiver is an electronic device. 电视接收器是一种电子装置。 4. The giver benefits more than the receiver. 付出者比接受者收获得更多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fanatic', '[fə\'nætɪk]', 'n.狂热者；极端分子；盲信者 adj.狂热的；盲信的', '1. We call him a politics fanatic. 我们叫他政治狂。 2. My roommate is a fanatic of Michael Jordan. 我的室友是迈克尔·乔丹的狂热粉丝。 3. The religious fanatics flagellated themselves. 狂热的宗教信仰者鞭打自己。 4. She\'s fanatic about pop music. 她对流行音乐很狂热。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kinetic', '[kɪ\'netɪk]', 'adj.运动的；动力学的', '1. Kinetic energy is a scalar property of motion. 动能是运动的一种标量属性。 2. Bodies traveling in a gravitational field are always undergoing an exchange of gravitational and kinetic energy. 在重力场中运动的物体会不停地改变其动能与重力位能。 3. By the research of the ethylene slurry polymerization mechanism and kinetics, the corresponding kinetic and moment ordinary differential equations were built and solved. 在研究了淤浆法乙烯聚合反应机理与动力学的基础上，建立并求解了相应的动力学与矩常微分方程组。', '副词: kinetically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('status', '[\'steɪtəs]', 'n.地位；情形；状况，状态；身份', '1. Women\'s social status has changed much over the years. 这些年来妇女的社会地位有了很大改变。 2. I\'ll keep you posted on the status. 我会随时告诉你进展的情形。 3. We ask the bank to report on his financial status. 我们请银行报告他的财政状况。 4. There are many fine shadings of status through the social hierarchy. 在各个社会等级之间有许多细微的身分区别。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('handy', '[\'hændi]', 'adj.方便的；手边的；灵巧的；近便的；现成的', '1. An electric kettle is very handy. 电水壶使用非常方便。 2. The sailors clung to anything handy. 水手们紧紧抓住手边任何东西。 3. He is very handy at repairing clocks. 他修钟表很灵巧。 4. It is quite a handy little sailing boat. 这是一个相当灵巧的小帆船。', '比较级: handier 最高级: handiest 名词: handiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('omit', '[ə\'mɪt]', 'vt.省略；遗漏；忘记；删去', '1. In writing telegrams omit superfluous words. 写电报稿要省去不必要的文字。 2. I could omit the overseas section at this point. 我可以暂时把海外部分省略掉。 3. Don\'t omit his name from the list. 名单上不要遗漏了他的名字。 4. Don\'t omit locking the door. 别忘了锁门。', '过去式: omitted 过去分词: omitted 现在分词: omitting 第三人称单数: omits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remodel', '[ˌriː\'mɑːdl]', 'v.重新塑造；改建；改制；改编', '1. I\'ll remodel the downstairs bedroom first. 我先要装修楼下那间房间。 2. Ask to remodel the way of working. 被要求改变工作的方式。 3. You only need money to remodel your weapon. 玩家改造武器只需要钱。 4. Remodel our home. / Buy a new home. 改建我们的房子。/买新房。', '名词: remodeler 过去式: remodeled/remodelled 过去分词: remodeled/remodelled 现在分词: remodeling/remodelling 第三人称单数: remodels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('optimal', '[\'ɑːptɪməl]', 'adj.最理想的；最佳的', '1. The ergonomics of the new office were felt to be optimal. 新办公室工效设计因素感觉十分理想。 2. The forest bath is one of the optimal zoology spots. 森林浴最理想最优良的生态场所。 3. Aerobic exercise is the optimal method for women attempting to lose weight. 有氧锻炼是女性减肥的最佳方式。 4. We have lost the optimal time to annihilate the enemy. 我们失去了歼灭敌人的最好时机。', '副词: optimally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cart', '[kɑːrt]', 'n.【C】(二轮或四轮)运货马车；手推车 vt.<非正式>(用手推车)运送；(用力；粗鲁地)拖', '1. Don\'t put the cart before the horse. [谚]勿本末倒置。 2. The heavy cart rumbled down the street. 笨重的马车辘辘地在街上走过。 3. The cart is piled high with fruit and vegetables. 马车上堆满了水果和蔬菜。 4. They were shoveling coal into a cart. 他们在把煤铲进手推车。 5. We had to cart our luggage up six flights of stairs. 我们得把行李提着上六段楼梯。', '形容词: cartable 名词: carter 过去式: carted 过去分词: carted 现在分词: carting 第三人称单数: carts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('influential', '[ˌɪnflu\'enʃl]', 'adj.有权势的；有影响的 n.有影响力的人物', '1. He used his influential friends to help him get into the civil service by the back door. 他利用那些有权有势的朋友帮助他走后门,到政府行政部门任职。 2. You may be fated to have a very influential incarnation. 你可能注定是一种非常有权势的化身。 3. Influential friends helped him to get a good job. 有权势的朋友们帮他弄到一份美差。 4. She uses her influential friends to get jobs. 她利用有势力的朋友找到工作。 5. He met a select group of media influentials. 他会见了一群经过挑选的媒介巨头。', '副词: influentially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('margin', '[\'mɑːrdʒən]', 'n.边缘；余地；幅度；利润；差额；页边空白；定金；【商】原价和卖价之差 vt.加边于；为…付保证金', '1. We came to the margin of the wood. 我们来到树林的边缘。 2. We allowed a margin of 20 minutes in catching the train. 我们有20分钟的余地赶火车。 3. There is no margin for error in our plan. 我们的计划中不留有误差幅度。 4. Our pricing policy aims at producing a 35% gross margin. 我们的定价政策目的在于赢得35%的毛利润。 5. The shore was margined with foam. 岸边都是泡沫。', '形容词: margined 过去式: margined 过去分词: margined 现在分词: margining 第三人称单数: margins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mania', '[\'meɪniə]', 'n. 狂热； 癖好； [医]躁狂 suf. ... 狂； 对 ... 有过分的热情', '1. Strictly,mania is a kind of madness which makes people violent. 严格地说，狂热是一种使人极端性的精神病。 2. French potholer, Berger, is a mania for cave exploration. 法国洞穴探险家伯杰是一位洞穴探险的狂热爱好者。 3. Mania is a habit we develop for a long time. 癖好是长时间形成的一种习惯。 4. Collecting small items can easily become a mania. 收藏零星物品往往容易变成一种癖好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('congress', '[\'kɑːŋɡrəs]', 'n.代表大会；议会 n.立法机关 n.国会<美>', '1. This matter will be discussed in congress tomorrow. 这个问题将在明天的代表大会上讨论。 2. The National People\'s Congress is the supreme organ of state power. 全国人民代表大会是最高国家权力机关。 3. The mayor must make policies in accordance with the bill passed in the Congress. 市长要根据议会的议案来制定政策。 4. A new peace initiative was approved by Mexico\'s congress. 墨西哥立法机关通过了一项最新的和平方案。', '形容词: congressional 副词: congressionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fraternal', '[frə\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.兄弟的；兄弟般的；[生]异卵双生的', '1. We\'ll do all we can to step up our aid to our fraternal countries. 我们将尽力加强对兄弟国家的援助。 2. The party sent its fraternal greetings to the trade union meeting. 党向工会大会致以亲切的问候。 3. In other words, their senses of what was fair were similar.No such correlations were seen in the behaviour of fraternal twins. 换句话说，他们的公平感是很相似的，而在异卵双生的双胞胎中就没有发现这样的关系。', '副词: fraternally 名词: fraternalism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flock', '[flɑːk]', 'n.一群；兽群；大堆；群众；羊群 v.聚集；成群而行', '1. There are many flocks of tourists in the palace. 宫殿里有好几群游客。 2. A flock of sheep poured through the gate. 一群羊从羊圈口涌了出来。 3. People came in flocks to see the royal procession. 人们蜂拥而至瞻望皇室人员外出时的仪仗队。 4. A few sheep have been lost from the flock. 羊群里少了几只羊。 5. Huge numbers of birds have flocked together by the lake. 成群的鸟聚集在湖畔。', '过去式: flocked 过去分词: flocked 现在分词: flocking 第三人称单数: flocks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acumen', '[\'ækjəmən]', 'n.敏锐；聪明', '1. His business acumen helped him to succeed where others had failed. 他在商业上的敏锐帮他在其他人失败的地方获得成功。 2. Her business acumen has made her very successful. 她灵活的经商头脑使她的生意十分兴隆。 3. The Parisian police, so much extolled for acumen, are cunning, but no more. 巴黎警察一向以聪明称道于世，其实不过是狡猾罢了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complex', '[kəm\'pleks]', 'adj.复杂的；合成的；复合的 n.综合体；复合体；[医]综合症状；[心]情结', '1. It was a complex problem. 这是一个复杂的问题。 2. This enhances the complex flavors and bouquet of the wine. 这加强了酒的合成的味道。 3. Complex briary fruit with smoldering oak. 有复合的水果香和烟熏橡木香。 4. They also provide composable functionality required to support complex, large-scale systems. 并提供可复合的功能以支持复杂的大规模系统。 5. Libraries are great complexes of tiny items. 图书馆是细小类目的大综合体。', '副词: complexly 名词: complexness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gland', '[ɡlænd]', 'n.腺', '1. The prostate is a small gland in men. 前列腺是男性体内的一个小腺体。 2. Many tiny tubes connect each silk gland with a spinneret. 许多极细小的导管把每个造丝腺体与吐丝器相连。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sore', '[sɔːr]', 'adj.疼痛的；痛心的；恼火的；严重的 n.痛处；伤口', '1. My legs are sore from all that running yesterday. 我的腿因为昨天跑步而感到酸痛。 2. Losing the election was a sore disappointment. 竞选失败令人痛心失望。 3. She\'s still a bit sore after the accident. 她出事后直到现在还觉得痛呢。 4. Don\'t get sore; I didn\'t mean it! 别生气，我不是故意的！ 5. He had a sore on his foot. 他的脚疼。', '比较级: sorer 最高级: sorest 名词: soreness 过去式: sored 过去分词: sored 现在分词: soring 第三人称单数: sores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drastic', '[\'dræstɪk]', 'adj.激烈的；重大的；极端的', '1. His view brings a drastic argument. 他的观点引起激烈的争论。 2. Drastic measures were taken to combat inflation. 已采取激烈措施对付通货膨胀。 3. Talk to me before you do anything drastic. 你采取任何重大行动之前要跟我谈谈。 4. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。', '副词: drastically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enslave', '[ɪn\'sleɪv]', 'vt.使做奴隶；使处于奴役的状态', '1. Someone was enslaved to her. 有人做了她的奴隶。 2. He is enslaved by love. 他正沉溺于爱情。 3. Her beauty enslaved many young men. 她的美貌倾倒了很多男青年。 4. Education makes people easy to govern but impossible to enslave. 教育使人容易去管理，但不可能去奴役。', '名词: enslavement 过去式: enslaved 过去分词: enslaved 现在分词: enslaving 第三人称单数: enslaves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slump', '[slʌmp]', 'v.大幅度下跌；猛然瘫坐；使倒下 n.暴跌；低潮状态；(土地)下沉', '1. Sales have slumped in the last month. 上月销售量骤降。 2. Business slumped after the holiday. 节日过后生意下降了。 3. She slumped, exhausted, onto the sofa. 她疲惫之极地倒在沙发上 4. He swayed forward and slumped down in his chair. 他身子向前一歪,猛地倒在靠椅里。 5. The slump hit his business hard. 物价暴跌使他的生意大受打击。', '过去式: slumped 过去分词: slumped 现在分词: slumping 第三人称单数: slumps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('debris', '[də\'briː]', 'n.碎片；残骸', '1. Falling debris rained on us from above. 碎片从上面像雨点儿一样落在我们身上。 2. They hunted through the debris on the floor to find the ring. 他们找遍了地板上的碎片去找戒指。 3. The sea throws up all sorts of debris on the beach. 大海把各种残骸碎片都冲上海滩。 4. Emergency teams are still clearing the debris from the plane crash. 各抢救小组仍在清理失事飞机的残骸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('estate', '[ɪ\'steɪt]', 'n.财产；遗产；房地产；状态；庄园', '1. The residue of estate belongs to his son. 剩余财产属于他的儿子。 2. He settled part of his estate on his son. 他把部分财产转让给儿子了。 3. The old man left an estate of two million dollars when he died. 那老人去世时留下二百万美元的遗产。 4. He owns a large estate in Scotland. 他在苏格兰有大量地产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attorney', '[ə\'tɜːrni]', 'n.(辩护)律师', '1. He became a prominent attorney. 他成了有名的律师。 2. His uncle obtained an attorney for him. 他的叔叔为他请了律师。 3. The attorney is working in a divorce case. 律师正忙于一个离婚案件。', '名词: attorneyship 名词复数: attorneys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reign', '[reɪn]', 'n.君主统治；在位期 v.统治；支配', '1. He has a tyrannical reign on his empire. 他是个残暴的皇帝。 2. People will remember the tyrannies of his reign. 人们不会忘记他统治时期的暴行。 3. The reign of Queen Victoria lasted more than sixty years. 维多利亚女王的统治持续了六十多年。 4. The American Revolution took place during the reign of George III. 美国独立战争发生在英王乔治三世统治时期。 5. He reigned over the country for forty years. 他统治了这个国家四十年。', '过去式: reigned 过去分词: reigned 现在分词: reigning 第三人称单数: reigns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inscribe', '[ɪn\'skraɪb]', 'v.题写；题赠；铭刻于；铭记 （英）登记. [数] 使内接.', '1. Will you inscribe your name in the book? 能否请你在这本书上签名? 2. To inscribe a poem on a painting is what painters like to do. 画家们爱在画上题诗。 3. I told the jeweler to inscribe the ring with my name. 我叫珠宝商把我的名字刻在那只戒指上。 4. My father\'s words are inscribed on my memory. 父亲的话我铭记於心。', '名词: inscriber 过去式: inscribed 过去分词: inscribed 现在分词: inscribing 第三人称单数: inscribes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('partisan', '[\'pɑːrtəzn]', 'adj.偏袒的；党派性的 n.强烈支持者；党羽；游击队员', '1. You must listen to both points of view and try not to be partisan. 你必须兼听双方观点 2. The other obstacle is partisan bickering. 另一个障碍是党派间的纷争。 3. He is a staunch partisan of the Republican Party. 他是共和党的坚定支持者。 4. Partisan politics is often an obstruction to good government. 党羽的政治阴谋常是良好政府的阻碍。', '名词: partisanship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outwit', '[ˌaʊt\'wɪt]', 'v.瞒骗；以智取胜', '1. Two prisoners outwitted their guards and got away. 有两个囚犯设计欺骗了警卫而逃走了。 2. Somehow he always manages to outwit his opponents. 他反正总能设法智胜对手。', '过去式: outwitted 过去分词: outwitted 现在分词: outwitting 第三人称单数: outwits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nonsense', '[\'nɑːnsens]', 'n.废话；胡说；荒唐', '1. You are talking complete nonsense. 你说的全是废话。 2. I have never in my entire life heard such nonsense! 我一生中从未听到过这样的废话！ 3. What he said is nonsense. 他的话纯粹是胡说。 4. We\'ll have no nonsense of that sort. 我们不能允许那种荒唐的事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('similar', '[\'sɪmələr]', 'adj.类似的', '1. The two buildings are similar on the whole. 从整体来看，这两幢楼是相似的。 2. I sympathize with you; I\'ve had a similar unhappy experience myself. 我很同情你，我自己也有过类似的不幸遭遇。 3. He talked about it in a similar way. 他对此事有相似的说法。 4. Gold is similar in color to brass. 金和铜颜色相仿。', '副词: similarly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frowzy', '[\'fraʊzɪ]', 'adj.不整洁的；臭的 =frowsy.', '1. Frowzy clothes; a frowzy professor. 脏衣服; 邋遢的教授 2. At London I am pent up in frowzy lodgings, where there is not room enough to swing a cat. 在伦敦，我守在肮脏的住所里面，那地方狭窄得无法转身。', '名词: frowziness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yield', '[jiːld]', 'v.生产；获利；屈服；弯下去 n.投资收益；生产量', '1. The village abounds in fields that yield many bushels of corn. 那个村庄到处都是盛产玉米的农田。 2. The combined investment is expected to yield $5,000 in the first year. 第一年该总投资有望获利5000美元。 3. We\' ve already made it clear that we will not yield to pressure. 我们已经表明我们不会屈服于压力。 4. The shelf is beginning to yield under that heavy weight. 架子被那么大的重量压得弯了下去。 5. So if the share price rises and the dividend does not, then the yield falls. 因此，如果股份上涨而股息不变，收益就下跌。', '名词: yielder 过去式: yielded 过去分词: yielded 现在分词: yielding 第三人称单数: yields');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('penal', '[\'piːnl]', 'adj.刑罚的；刑事的；严重的', '1. He underwent nineteen years of penal servitude for theft. 他因犯了大窃案受过十九年的苦刑。 2. After his experience in jail, he has a pretty jaundiced view of the penal system. 经历了牢狱生活之后，他对刑罚制度颇有成见。 3. Parliament may legislate on any matter of penal law. 议会可以对刑事法律的任何事项立法。 4. Voluntary surrender is an important system of penal institution in criminal law of China. 自首制度，是我国刑法中的一项重要刑罚制度。', '副词: penally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fare', '[fer]', 'n.车费；路费；乘客；食物 vi.过活；进展；进食；旅行；行走', '1. Let me go shares with you in the taxi fare. 我和你分摊计程车费吧。 2. She didn\'t have enough money for the bus fare. 她的钱不够付车费。 3. He didn\'t have enough money to pay his train fare. 他没有足够的钱来付火车费。 4. The normal return fare to New York is fifty-six. 去纽约的来回票标准价是56元。 5. How would I fare in a strange city? 在一个陌生的城市里，我怎么度日呢?', '名词: farer 过去式: fared 过去分词: fared 现在分词: faring 第三人称单数: fares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chip', '[tʃɪp]', 'n.缺口；碎屑；油炸土豆条；薄片；筹码；芯片；（足球）高球；（高尔夫球）近穴球 v.形成（缺口）；切下；凿下；凑份子；打高球；近穴击球；将（土豆等）切条', '1. It was difficult finding two cups without some kind of chip on them. 很难找到两个一点没有缺口的杯子。 2. A small chip of ice flew into the air. 一小块碎冰飞溅到了空中。 3. She had a hamburger and a portion of chip. 她吃了一个汉堡包和一份炸薯条。 4. I\'ve got chocolate chip for you. 我给你们买了巧克力薄片。 5. Be careful with these plates they chip very easily. 小心这些盘子--边缘容易破损。', '过去式: chipped 过去分词: chipped 现在分词: chipping 第三人称单数: chips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('residue', '[\'rezɪduː]', 'n.残渣；剩余物；[律]剩余财产', '1. The insoluble lead oxide is remained in the residue. 不溶性氧化物相留存在残渣中。 2. This is a kind of brandy distilled from grape or apple residue. 这是种渣酿白兰地酒，由葡萄或苹果残渣酿成的白兰地。 3. The flies leave a sticky residue on crops. 苍蝇在庄稼上留下黏糊糊的东西。 4. The residue of estate belongs to his son. 剩余财产属于他的儿子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diagonal', '[daɪ\'æɡənl]', 'adj.对角线的；斜的；斜纹的 n.对角线；斜线；斜列', '1. When 2 or 4 or 6 players, the diagonal play is your enemy. 2人、4人或6人游戏时与互为对角线的一方对抗， 2. Of course! My outlet is diagonal. 当然咯，我的插座是斜的。 3. The wood surface of the furniture is full of diagonal stripes. 这件家具的木头表面上布满了斜纹。 4. Each stitch covers a diagonal of one cell of the grid. 每条缝线覆盖格子的对角线。', '副词: diagonally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('watercourse', '[\'wɔːtərkɔːrs]', 'n.水流；河道；水道', '1. There are lots of chemicals that pollute the local watercourse. 大量化学物质污染着当地水流。 2. This river has a zigzagging watercourse and many branches. 这条河的河道曲折，汊流众多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cosmopolitan', '[ˌkɑːzmə\'pɑːlɪtən]', 'adj.世界性的；久经世故的；遍生于世界的；四海一家的 n.世界主义者', '1. New York is a highly cosmopolitan city. 纽约是一个高度世界性的城市。 2. Alexander envisioned a cosmopolitan culture in his new empire. 亚历山大打算让他的新帝国具有世界性的文化。 3. The rose is a cosmopolitan plant. 玫瑰是遍生于世界各地的植物。 4. She has a very cosmopolitan outlook on life. 她有四海一家的人生观。', '名词: cosmopolitanism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crumple', '[\'krʌmpl]', 'v.（使)起皱；(使)崩溃；压垮 n.压痕；皱痕', '1. He put on a crumpled suit. 他穿上一件皱巴巴的西装。 2. Silk dresses are easy to crumple up if not carefully handled. 真丝衣服若不能正确处理，很容易起皱。 3. The wall was likely to crumple up at any time. 墙随时可以坍掉。 4. Her resistance to the proposal has crumpled. 她对这个建议的抵触情绪已化为乌有了。', '形容词: crumply 过去式: crumpled 过去分词: crumpled 现在分词: crumpling 第三人称单数: crumples');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('verbal', '[\'vɜːbl]', 'adj.口头的；用言语的；用文字的；逐字的；动词的 n.动名词', '1. They had made a verbal agreement to sell. 他们达成了口头售货协定。 2. Don\'t be afraid of verbal abuse or criticism. 不要害怕口头上的辱骂或批评。 3. The teacher teaches us the verbal skills. 老师告诉我们使用言辞的技巧。 4. The verbal imagery has hardly changed. 语言文字的意象几乎没有改变。', '副词: verbally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deviate', '[\'diːvieɪt]', 'v.偏离；脱离 n.叛离者；偏差；不正常的人或物 adj.离经叛道的', '1. Don\'t always deviate to minor issues. 不要老是偏离到次要问题上去。 2. You will not deviate from your present course. 你不能偏离目前航线 3. His remarks usually deviate from truth. 他的话通常都与事实不符。 4. Do not deviate from the beaten track. 不要逸出常轨。', '形容词: deviatory 名词: deviator 过去式: deviated 过去分词: deviated 现在分词: deviating 第三人称单数: deviates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('finance', '[\'faɪnæns]', 'n.金融；财政；资金 vt.给 ... 提供资金；负担经费', '1. He is a well-known expert in finance. 他是知名的金融专家。 2. The Chancellor of the Exchequer is the minister in charge of finance in Britain. 英国财政大臣是负责财政的大臣。 3. Unless we can get more finance, we\'ll have to close the store. 除非我们能得到更多的资金，我们将不得不关闭这家商店。 4. The repairs to the school will be financed by the educational department. 学校的修缮将由教育部门出资。', '形容词: financeable 过去式: financed 过去分词: financed 现在分词: financing 第三人称单数: finances');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prerequisite', '[ˌpriː\'rekwəzɪt]', 'n.先决条件；前提 adj.作为前提的；必备的', '1. Careful study of the market is a prerequisite for success. 仔细研究市场情况是取得成功的先决条件。 2. Good muscles are one of the prerequisites of physical fitness. 肌肉发达是身体健康的一个必备条件。 3. Stability is a prerequisite for reform and development. 稳定是改革和发展的前提。 4. A sense of humour is prerequisite to understanding her work. 要理解她的作品就必须具有幽默感。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('choice', '[tʃɔɪs]', 'n.选择；挑选；抉择 adj.上等的；精选的', '1. I believe that he can make a judicious choice. 我相信他能作出明智的选择。 2. The choice rests entirely with you. 这完全由你来选择。 3. We have no choice except to trust ourselves. 我们必须依靠自己,没有其他选择。 4. He is cautious in his choice of words. 他措辞很谨慎。 5. We select only the choicest apples for our pies. 我们精选最好的苹果制作馅饼。', '副词: choicely 比较级: choicer 最高级: choicest 名词: choiceness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('breed', '[briːd]', 'v.繁殖；养育；引起，产生；教养 n.品种；血统', '1. Wild animals don\'t breed well in captivity. 野生动物圈养时不好繁殖。 2. How often do lions breed? 狮子多长时间产一次仔? 3. I breed some chicks for pets. 我养了一些小鸡当宠物。 4. Spartan youths were bred as warriors. 斯巴达青年被培养成战士. 5. Spaniel is a breed of dog with large ears. 西班牙猎狗是一种长着大耳朵的猎狗。', '过去式: bred 过去分词: bred 现在分词: breeding 第三人称单数: breeds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('zinc', '[zɪŋk]', 'n. 锌 vt. 在 ... 上镀锌', '1. The fusion of copper and zinc make the metal brass. 铜和锌的熔化制成黄铜。 2. Zinc is generally caustic to foliage. 锌常对幼叶有腐蚀作用。', '简写符号: Zn 过去式: zinced/zincked 过去分词: zinced/zincked 现在分词: zincing/zincking 第三人称单数: zincs/zincks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lumber', '[\'lʌmbər]', 'n.木材；木料 v.伐木 vi.缓慢地移动 vt.拖累', '1. I followed the road down past the piles of lumber. 我穿过成堆木材，沿着路走下去。 2. Iron mined in order to topple trees for lumber. 开采铁矿则是为了砍伐树木以获取木材。 3. They slapped together a cabin out of old lumber. 他们利用旧木料草草地盖起了一间小屋。 4. Among the sawmill customers are the chair factory and other users of cut lumber. 在锯木场的客户中是那些椅子工厂及其他木料用户。 5. He was a lumberjack, living in lumber camps of the American Northwest. 他是个伐木工，住在美国西北的伐木营地里。 6. He refused to lumber himself with a family. 他不愿有家室拖累。', '副词: lumberingly 名词: lumberer 过去式: lumbered 过去分词: lumbered 现在分词: lumbering 第三人称单数: lumbers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commit', '[kə\'mɪt]', 'v.犯罪；承诺；委托；托付', '1. They committed outrages on innocent citizens. 他们对无辜的市民犯下了暴行。 2. He committed suicide rather than sell out to the enemy. 他宁愿自杀而没有向敌人投降。 3. He didn\'t commit himself to anything. 他没有作任何承诺。 4. The girl was committed to the care of an aunt. 这女孩被交给姨母照顾。', '形容词: committable 过去式: committed 过去分词: committed 现在分词: committing 第三人称单数: commits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eloquence', '[\'eləkwəns]', 'n.雄辩；口才', '1. His eloquence did not avail against the facts. 他的雄辩在事实面前不起什么作用。 2. Eloquence and ignorance sometimes go together. 滔滔不绝的雄辩有时候是伴随着无知的。 3. She was charmed by his eloquence. 她被他的口才所倾倒。 4. He inherited his eloquence from his father, a Christian preacher. 他继承了他那个当基督教传教士的父亲的口才。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('explode', '[ɪk\'sploʊd]', 'vi.爆炸；激增；爆发 vt.使爆炸；驳倒', '1. The bomb was timed to explode during the rush-hour. 炸弹选在人最多时爆炸。 2. When the boiler exploded many people were injured. 因锅炉爆炸，许多人受了伤。 3. The firework exploded in his hand. 那个爆竹在他手里响了。 4. Investment in technology stocks exploded in the 1990s. 二十世纪九十年代的,对科技股票的投资迅速增加。 5. The children exploded three firecrackers. 孩子们燃放了三个爆竹', '名词: exploder 过去式: exploded 过去分词: exploded 现在分词: exploding 第三人称单数: explodes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assert', '[ə\'sɜːrt]', 'vt.断言；主张，坚持；生效；维护', '1. She asserted that he was innocent. 她断言，他是无罪的。 2. Upon inspection, we assert that the systems development process is empirical 通过以上分析,我们断言系统开发过程是经验的 3. We encouraged him to assert his view of the matter. 我们鼓励他坚持自己对此事的看法。 4. The laws of historical development will assert themselves. 历史发展的规律是不可抗拒的。', '形容词: assertable 名词: asserter 过去式: asserted 过去分词: asserted 现在分词: asserting 第三人称单数: asserts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stage', '[steɪdʒ]', 'n.舞台；戏剧；阶段；步骤；行程 v.上演；举行；组织；筹划；使出现', '1. She stood alone on the enormous stage. 她孤零零地站在巨大的舞台上。 2. He quitted the stage of politics. 他退出了政治舞台。 3. Novels are often adapted for the stage. 小说常常改编为戏剧。 4. The disease is still in its primary stage. 这疾病仍然在初发阶段。 5. She asserted that she was going to stage a musical comedy. 她说她要组织演出一部音乐喜剧。', '名词: stageful 过去式: staged 过去分词: staged 现在分词: staging 第三人称单数: stages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disrespectful', '[ˌdɪsrɪ\'spektfl]', 'adj.无礼的；不尊敬的', '1. The disrespectful boy laughed at his father. 那个无礼的男孩嘲笑自己的父亲。 2. There was nothing disrespectful in the call. 这种称呼并没有不尊敬的意思。', '副词: disrespectfully 名词: disrespectfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('doze', '[doʊz]', 'v.打瞌睡 n.瞌睡', '1. He dozed off during the class. 他上课打瞌睡。 2. He closed his eyes and seemed to doze. 他闭上眼睛，好像在打瞌睡。 3. We couldn\'t help but doze off during his lecture. 他演讲时我们不得不打瞌睡。 4. He fell into a doze. 他打起盹儿来了。', '名词: dozer 过去式: dozed 过去分词: dozed 现在分词: dozing 第三人称单数: dozes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('numb', '[nʌm]', 'adj.麻木的；失去知觉的 vt.使麻木；使失去知觉', '1. My fingers were so numb that I could hardly write. 我的手指都麻木了几乎不能写字。 2. I\'ve just been to the dentist and my face is still numb. 我刚刚去看了牙医，脸上现在还没知觉呢。 3. The anaesthetic made his whole face go numb. 麻醉药使他的整张脸失去了知觉。 4. His leg was numbed by the intense pain. 他的腿因剧痛而麻木。', '副词: numbly 比较级: number 最高级: numbest 名词: numbness 过去式: numbed 过去分词: numbed 现在分词: numbing 第三人称单数: numbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feasible', '[\'fiːzəbl]', 'adj.可行的；可能的', '1. The plan did not seem feasible. 这个计划似乎没法实行。 2. It\'s quite clear that the electric car is technically feasible. 电动汽车明显在工艺技术上是可行的。 3. It\'s not feasible to follow your proposals. 按照你的建议去做是行不通的。 4. It\'s not feasible to dismiss him. 不可开除他。', '副词: feasibly 名词: feasibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('symptom', '[\'sɪmptəm]', 'n.症状；征兆', '1. Cigarettes can aggravate the symptoms of a cold. 抽烟会加重感冒症状。 2. The doctor made his diagnosis after studying the patient\'s symptoms. 医生研究病人的症状后, 作出诊断。 3. Fever is a symptom of many illnesses. 发烧是许多疾病的症兆。', '形容词: symptomless');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('populate', '[\'pɑːpjuleɪt]', 'v.构成人口；居住于；【计】填入', '1. Carcasses populate the brush, their putrid remains swallowed whole by the land. 尸体居住于刷子，他们的腐败遗骸由土地吞下了整体。 2. All sea life upon Earth originates from these two breeding tanks in which those species that could flourish went on to populate all oceans. 地球上所有海洋生命都起源于这两个培育槽，在其中那些物种能繁荣，接着居住于所有海洋。', '过去式: populated 过去分词: populated 现在分词: populating 第三人称单数: populates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hasty', '[\'heɪsti]', 'adj.匆匆的；轻率的；急忙的', '1. Some people are prone to jump to hasty conclusions. 有些人往往作出轻率的结论。', '副词: hastily 比较级: hastier 最高级: hastiest 名词: hastiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('paramount', '[\'pærəmaʊnt]', 'adj.极为重要的；至高无上的 n.最高统治者 Paramount. n.派拉蒙(美电影公司)', '1. This matter is of paramount importance. 此事至关重要。 2. The reduction of unemployment should be paramount. 降低失业率应是头等大事。 3. These constitutions are paramount. 这些宪法至高无上。 4. This duty is paramount to all the others. 没有比这更重要的义务了。 5. MGM, Paramount, and Columbia are all majors in film industry. 米高梅、派拉蒙和哥伦比亚都是电影业的大公司。', '副词: paramountly 名词: paramountcy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('correspond', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːnd]', 'v.符合；对应；通信', '1. Your account and hers correspond. 你的说法跟她的说法一致。 2. Your account of events corresponds with hers. 你说的情况跟她说的相符。 3. The American Congress corresponds to the British Parliament. 美国的国会相当于英国的议会。 4. I correspond with him regularly. 我经常和他通信。', '过去式: corresponded 过去分词: corresponded 现在分词: corresponding 第三人称单数: corresponds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('willow', '[\'wɪloʊ]', 'n.柳树；柳木制品', '1. You\'d better hack off the branch of that willow. 你最好把那棵柳树的枝丫砍掉。 2. A willow is a brush painting spring scenery. 一株柳树，是一支描绘春天的彩笔。', '过去式: willowed 过去分词: willowed 现在分词: willowing 第三人称单数: willows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elite', '[eɪ\'liːt]', 'n.精英 adj.精英的；优秀的', '1. The elite are the competitive focus of 21 century. 精英人才是21世纪国际间竞争的焦点。 2. It is a luxury brand established for the elite and the affluent. 这是一个为精英群体和富人所创设的奢侈品牌。 3. It is indubitable that he is an elite in information technology. 毫无疑问，他是信息技术界的精英。 4. Public opinion is influenced by the small elite who control the media. 舆论为少数控制着新闻媒介的上层人士所左右。 5. This is an elite group reserved for members only. 这是仅为会员保留的精英小组。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('identity', '[aɪ\'dentəti]', 'n.一致；身份；特征', '1. Identity of interests is the bond that unites them. 利害的一致是把他们联合起来的纽带。 2. The police asked him to show his identity card. 警察让他出示身份证。 3. The journalist did not want to reveal the identity of his informant. 那个新闻工作者不想透露消息提供人的身分。 4. He had to make his identity public. 他不得不公开自己的身份。', '名词复数: identities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brink', '[brɪŋk]', 'n.边缘；边沿；界限', '1. Natalie is living on the brink of panic. 娜塔丽正生活在痛苦的边缘。 2. She knows well that she and Louis are on a brink. 她深深知道，她和路易斯是到了危险的边沿。 3. Prosecutors said he left Enron because he knew the company was on the brink of bankruptcy. 检察官说他离开的原因是因为他知道公司已经处于破产的边沿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shameless', '[\'ʃeɪmləs]', 'adj.无耻的', '1. He is a shameless cheat. 他是个无耻的骗子。 2. She unshelled his shameless lies. 她揭露了他的无耻谎言。 3. She\'s quite shameless about wearing pajamas at work. 她穿着睡衣上班却不觉羞耻。', '副词: shamelessly 名词: shamelessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decrease', '[dɪ\'kriːs]', 'v.减少；减小；降低 n.减少；降低', '1. They are making further efforts to decrease military spending. 他们正在做进一步的努力来减少军费开支。 2. His interest in this subject gradually decreases. 他对这门学科的兴趣逐渐减退。 3. The government projected a tax decrease. 政府计划降低税收。 4. They tried to decrease the costs. 他们设法降低成本。 5. The new treatment led to a huge decrease in the number of deaths. 新的疗法使死亡率急剧减少。', '副词: decreasingly 过去式: decreased 过去分词: decreased 现在分词: decreasing 第三人称单数: decreases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aspiration', '[ˌæspə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.抱负；热望；志向；渴望 n.吸引术；抽吸；吸气；发送气音', '1. His true aspiration is to become the President of the United States. 他真正的抱负是想成为美国总统。 2. He nursed an aspiration to be a poet. 他心怀当诗人的愿望。 3. The generalship was his aspiration. 将官之职位是他梦寐以求的目标。 4. These are not just my goals, but our common aspiration. 这些不仅仅是我的目标,而且是我们的共同志向。 5. Aspiration cytologic examination reealed a fibrocystic change. 抽吸细胞学检查为纤维囊性变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relevant', '[\'reləvənt]', 'adj.相关的；切题的；中肯的；有重大关系的；有意义的，目的明确的', '1. A paper relevant to this research was published by him. 与本研究相关的一篇论文是他发表的。 2. Have you heard of the relevant report? 你听说过相关的报道吗? 3. My next conclusion is more relevant. 我的另一个结论更切题。 4. Portraits of people will draw readers\'attention, especially if the images are relevant and tell a story. 人物肖像可以吸引读者的注意,当图像切题并在讲述一个故事时更是如此。', '副词: relevantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infancy', '[\'ɪnfənsi]', 'n.婴儿期；幼年；初期 [法律]未成年.', '1. Children are in their infancy when they are babies. 孩子们还是小宝宝时，是处于婴儿期。 2. Children treated during infancy or early childhood are at the highest risk. 被治疗的孩子处于婴儿期或幼年时期是高度危险期。 3. I\'m sure you have heard of his precarious infancy. 我相信你们都曾听说过他多灾多难的幼年。 4. Tadpoles are the infancy form of frogs. 蝌蚪是青蛙的幼年形态。', '名词复数: infancies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consecrate', '[\'kɑːnsɪkreɪt]', 'v.供神用；奉献；使神圣 adj.被献给神的；神圣的', '1. Who then is willing to consecrate himself this day to the Lord? 今日有谁乐意将自己献给耶和华呢。 2. A doctor\'s life is consecrated to curing sick people. 医生献身于医治病人。 3. I solemnly pledge myself to consecrate my life to the service of humanity. 我郑重地保证自己要奉献一切为人类服务。 4. Who then is willing to consecrate himself this day to the Lord? 今日有谁乐意将自己献给耶和华呢。', '形容词: consecrative 名词: consecrator 过去式: consecrated 过去分词: consecrated 现在分词: consecrating 第三人称单数: consecrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grab', '[ɡræb]', 'v.抓住；攫取 n.抓取物；抓', '1. Grab a seat and make yourself at home. 随便找个地方坐，别客气。 2. Let\'s grab a sandwich and go to see the film. 让我们赶快吃个三明治就去看电影吧。 3. He grabbed my collar and pulled me towards him. 他抓住我的领子把我拉倒他面前。 4. When I gave him the chance, he grabbed it at once. 我给他这一机会，他立刻抓住不放。 5. The job is up for grabs. Why don\'t you apply now? 那工作谁都可以争取。你怎么不现在就申请呢？', '名词: grabber 过去式: grabbed 过去分词: grabbed 现在分词: grabbing 第三人称单数: grabs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revolution', '[ˌrevə\'luːʃn]', 'n.革命；变革；重大改变；旋转', '1. Most countries have had revolutions aganist the government. 大多数国家发生过反对政府的革命。 2. The industrial revolution had taken place in England first. 工业革命首先在英国发生。 3. Those people go around preaching revolution. 那些人到处宣扬革命。 4. The invention of aircraft caused a revolution in our ways of travelling. 飞机的发明引起了旅行方式的巨大改变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stiff', '[stɪf]', 'adj.硬的；僵直的；艰难的；生硬的；拘谨的；烈性的 adv.极其；僵硬地 n.死尸；流浪汉；过于拘谨的人；吝啬鬼；醉鬼', '1. Shoes are often stiff when they are new. 新鞋刚穿起来常常都是硬邦邦的。 2. She cleaned the sink with a stiff brush. 她用硬毛刷清洗水槽。 3. His legs felt stiff from having sat for so long. 由于坐得太久，他的双腿感到僵直。 4. He has to take a stiff test before he is qualified. 在取得资格之前,他必须通过一次艰难的考试。 5. The opera bored me stiff. 这个歌剧真把我腻烦透了。', '形容词: stiffish 副词: stiffly 比较级: stiffer 最高级: stiffest 名词: stiffness 过去式: stiffed 过去分词: stiffed 现在分词: stiffing 第三人称单数: stiffs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('supplement', '[\'sʌplɪmənt]', 'n.增刊；补充物 vt.增补；补充', '1. It comes out each week and it has a magazine supplement. 每周出版一期，还附有杂志增刊。 2. The upset supplement supplier went up with the puppet to the upper room for supper. 心烦意乱的增刊供给者与傀儡一起到上面的房间吃晚餐。 3. The money I got was a useful supplement to my ordinary income. 我得到的那笔钱是很管用的外快。 4. Man\'s work is rather the needful supplement to himself than the outcome of it. 一个人的工作更多地是他自身的必要补充,而非这种补充的结果。 5. She gives private lessons to supplement her income. 她给私人授课以贴补收入。', '形容词: supplementary 名词: supplementarity 过去式: supplemented 过去分词: supplemented 现在分词: supplementing 第三人称单数: supplements');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('soybean', '[\'sɔɪbiːn]', 'n.大豆；黄豆', '1. The soybean can serve as a meat substitute. 大豆有时可以替代肉类。 2. Rapeseed oil, and soybean oil are good for health. 菜籽油和大豆油对人体都有好处。 3. Tofu we often eat is made from soybean curds. 我们经常吃的豆腐就是用黄豆磨成的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('redeem', '[rɪ\'diːm]', 'vt.赎回；弥补；履行；兑现；偿还；解救', '1. She redeemed her reputation with a powerful speech to the party convention. 她由于向党代表大会做了有力的演说而挽回了自己的声誉。 2. I redeemed my watch from the pawnshop. 我从当铺赎回了手表。 3. The sole redeeming feature of this job is the salary. 这份工作唯其薪水尚可弥补一切之不足。 4. Jones redeemed his earlier poor performance by scoring two goals. 琼斯射入两球方弥补其初时表现之不足。', '形容词: redeemable 过去式: redeemed 过去分词: redeemed 现在分词: redeeming 第三人称单数: redeems');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gloomy', '[\'ɡluːmi]', 'adj.阴暗的；忧闷的；前景黯淡的', '1. Being alone in that gloomy house gave me the willies. 我一个人在那所阴暗的房子心里就发毛。 2. A few faint gleams of sunshine lit up the gloomy afternoon. 有几束隐约的阳光使阴暗的下午有些明亮。 3. Her smile is a breath of fresh air in this gloomy office. 她的微笑给沉闷的办公室带来生气。 4. There is a gloomy, overcast expression on his face. 他愁眉苦脸。', '副词: gloomily 比较级: gloomier 最高级: gloomiest 名词: gloominess');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sweeping', '[\'swiːpɪŋ]', 'n.扫除 （复数）sweepings: 垃圾. adj.一扫而去的；凶猛的；广泛的 动词sweep的现在分词.', '1. The gardener is sweeping up the leaves in the road. 园林工人正在扫除道上的落叶。 2. It was like new air, or sweeping cobwebs. 这就像呼吸新鲜空气或扫除蜘蛛网时的感觉。 3. With the world economy mired in recession, Mr. Obama said there should be no illusion that producing the sweeping changes needed for success at Copenhagen will be easy. 随着世界经济陷入衰退，奥巴马先生说，我们不该有在哥本哈根能够轻易发生成功所需的一扫而去的变化的错觉。 4. He will never agree that a sweeping passion is a ravaging torrent which fatally leads a man to certain acts and is therefore an excuse. 他决不会赞同这样的观点，即势不可挡的激情是一种凶猛的激流，使人产生某些行为，因而是一种理由。', '副词: sweepingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('myth', '[mɪθ]', 'n.神话；虚构的故事', '1. This is the story of a myth of our times. 这是一个关于我们这个时代的神话故事。 2. Venus is one of the goddess in Greek myth. 维纳斯是希腊神话中的女神之一。 3. The rich uncle of whom he boasts is only a myth. 他吹嘘的那个有钱的叔叔只是个乌有翁。 4. His story about is very wealthy is a complete myth. 关于他非常富有的说法完全是捏造出来的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('marine', '[mə\'riːn]', 'adj.海的；海事的；海生的；航海的 n.海运业；船舶；水兵', '1. His father is a marine biologist. 他父亲是位海洋生物学家。 2. Water pollution imperils all kinds of marine life. 水质污染危及所有海洋生物。 3. He works for the marine court. 他为海事法庭工作。 4. The rocks are covered by marine plants. 岩石被海生植物所覆盖。 5. He sought an officer\'s berth in the merchant marine. 他在商船上找了一个高级船员的职位。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('calcium', '[\'kælsiəm]', 'n.钙', '1. We need some calcium everyday. 我们每天需要些钙。 2. I have a slight calcium deficiency. 我有点缺钙。 3. Like most dairy products, such as milk and cheese, yogurt contains a lot of calcium. 像大部分的乳制品，如牛奶和奶酪一样，优酪乳含有许多钙质。', '简写符号: Ca');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lightning', '[\'laɪtnɪŋ]', 'n.闪电；意外的幸运 adj.闪电般的；快速的', '1. The little girl is afraid of thunder and lightning. 这小女孩害怕雷声和闪电。 2. The tree was struck by lightning and splintered. 那棵树被闪电劈裂了。 3. He drove the car with lightning speed. 他以闪电般的速度开车。 4. He would shoot his water-pot into the tank with a lightning movement so as to get his supply from an uncontaminated depth. 他用闪电般的速度把水桶戳进水池里，以便能从没被污染的深处取水。', '过去式: lightninged 过去分词: lightninged 现在分词: lightning 第三人称单数: lightnings');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('carve', '[kɑːrv]', 'v.雕刻；切割', '1. The statue was carved out of marble. 这座雕像是用大理石雕刻的。 2. We will look for a pumpkin, to carve into a jack-o-lantern. 我们将要找一颗南瓜来雕刻成南瓜灯。 3. He carved me some very nice pieces of chicken. 他为我切了几块很好的鸡肉。 4. It\'s your turn to carve the meat. 该你来把肉切开了。', '名词: carver 过去式: carved 过去分词: carved 现在分词: carving 第三人称单数: carves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('raise', '[reɪz]', 'n.上升；增高；高地 vt.升起；举起；饲养；提出；引起；筹集，募集', '1. The percentage of the pay raise equals the increase in prices. 薪水的提高比率和物价的上升一致。 2. He got a raise in monthly wages. 他的月薪增加了。 3. The first thing that we did when we conquered the town was to haul down the enemy\'s flag and raise our own. 我们占领这座城市以后以后所做的第一件事就是降下城里敌人的旗帜，升起我们自己的旗帜。 4. The guesture might come from Rome, when people raise the right hand to show their extolling and respect for the empire. 这一手势有可能来自罗马,那时人们将右臂举起以表示对帝王的称颂或敬意。', '名词: raiser 过去式: raised 过去分词: raised 现在分词: raising 第三人称单数: raises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('household', '[\'haʊshoʊld]', 'n.家庭；户 adj.家庭的；家喻户晓的', '1. The whole household got up early last Sunday. 上个星期天全家人都起得很早。 2. He peddled small articles around the town from household to household. 他在镇上挨家挨户兜售一些小件物品。 3. I disputed with my wife on household expenses. 我跟太太争论有关家庭费用的问题。 4. Microsoft has become a household word. 微软已经成为一个家喻户晓的名词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cumbersome', '[\'kʌmbərsəm]', 'adj.笨重的；不方便的', '1. The grizzly bear looked cumbersome and awkward. 灰熊看上去又笨拙又迟钝。 2. This arrangement is cumbersome to manage. 如此安排繁琐得难以管理。 3. They are cumbersome on land, but stealthy and sleek in the water. 它们在陆地上行动笨拙但在水里却敏捷灵活。 4. A tabulation of a function of two variables is cumbersome, but possible. 二元函数的列表法是不方便的，然而是可能的。', '副词: cumbersomely');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('audio', '[\'ɔːdioʊ]', 'adj.声音的；成音频率的 n.音频；音响设备', '1. The reproductive quality of audio tapes has improved enormously. 录音磁带的复制质量有了很大改进。 2. Voice commands could not set the audio device. 声音命令无法设置音频设备。 3. Music, of course, is just a special case of general audio, but an important one. 当然，音乐是声波的一种特殊情况，但却是重要的一种。 4. In audio, a very low frequency oscillation often resulting from a positive feedback path in an amplifier system. 在音响设备中出现的振荡频率极低的低频振荡，常因放大系统的正反馈回路引起。', '名词复数: audios');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tense', '[tens]', 'adj.紧张的；绷紧的；拉紧的 v.拉紧；使紧绷 n.(动词)时态', '1. Try to act naturally, even if you\'re tense. 即使紧张也不要做作。 2. It is difficult to be natural when one is tense. 人在紧张的时候很难泰然自若。 3. She was gently massaging the tense muscles of his neck. 她温柔地按摩着他脖子上绷紧的肌肉。 4. She tensed, hearing that noise again. 她再次听到那个声音就紧张起来。 5. The verb is in the present tense. 这个动词使用的是现在时态。', '副词: tensely 比较级: tenser 最高级: tensest 名词: tenseness 过去式: tensed 过去分词: tensed 现在分词: tensing 第三人称单数: tenses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('former', '[\'fɔːrmər]', 'adj.前者的；前任的；以前的 n.创造者；<英>学校某一年级的学生', '1. Of these two men, the former is dead but the latter is still alive. 这两个人中，前者已死，而后者仍然活着。 2. Mr. Heath is the former Prime Minister of Britain. 希思先生是英国前任首相。 3. I paid a visit to my former English teacher. 我拜访了我以前的英语老师。 4. Many of his former supporters voted against him. 他以前的许多支持者投票反对他。 5. a former of ideas 想出主意者', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('snack', '[snæk]', 'n.小吃；点心 vi.吃点心', '1. We are in a hurry so we have to make doing with a quick snack . 我们时间很紧,只好胡乱吃了顿小吃 2. Usually I only have a snack at lunchtime. 我中午通常只吃点心。 3. Apples are a more nutritional snack than popcorn. 苹果是比爆米花更有营养的零食。 4. If you snack too much, you may get fat. 零食吃的太多,你会长胖的。', '名词: snacker 过去式: snacked 过去分词: snacked 现在分词: snacking 第三人称单数: snacks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plain', '[pleɪn]', 'adj.清楚的；简单的；坦白的；平常的；朴素的；纯的 n.平原；广阔的区域 adv.完全地；纯粹地', '1. It was plain to everyone that she was not happy. 她并不幸福,这是明摆着的事实。 2. The restaurant serves plain home-made meals. 那个餐馆供应简单的家常菜。 3. She was admired for her plain speaking. 她说话坦白,这一点令人钦佩。 4. Most people see great men as wizards; however, they are just plain people. 大多数人觉得伟人是奇才,然而,他们只不过是平常人。 5. The wind whipped across the plain. 大风扫过平原。 6. Beck went plain crazy with anger on the day when he received his Dear John from his girlfriend. 贝克收到他女朋友的绝交信的那天简直都气疯了。', '副词: plainly 比较级: plainer 最高级: plainest 名词: plainness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inconspicuous', '[ˌɪnkən\'spɪkjuəs]', 'adj.不显眼的；不引人注意的；难以觉察的', '1. He will drag her off to parties, and she spends the whole evening trying to look inconspicuous in some corner. 他要把她拉到宴会上去，她整个晚上都试图躲在不显眼的角落。 2. The shy girl tried to make herself as inconspicuous as possible. 那个怕羞的女孩子尽量使自己不被人注意。', '副词: inconspicuously 名词: inconspicuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('landscape', '[\'lændskeɪp]', 'n.风景；风景画；山水；[计]横向 v.美化景观', '1. The landscape unfolded before us. 那景色展现在我们面前。 2. Those cottages blend perfectly with the landscape. 那些农舍与周围的风景完全融为一体了。 3. I prefer landscape to still life. 我喜欢风景画，不喜欢静物画。 4. The moon shed a silver luster over the landscape. 月亮的银光流泻于山水间。 5. The area around the mill pond has also been landscaped. 贮木场周围都经过美化。', '名词: landscaper 过去式: landscaped 过去分词: landscaped 现在分词: landscaping 第三人称单数: landscapes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('integrity', '[ɪn\'teɡrəti]', 'n.完整；完善；正直；诚实', '1. We must respect each other\'s territorial integrity. 我们应当尊重彼此的领土完整。 2. We all have an interest in maintaining the integrity of the ecosystem. 维持生态系统的完整是我们共同的利益。 3. One of the most important features of the steel cables is their structural integrity. 钢索最重要的特点之一，是结构的完善性。 4. My husband is a man of the highest integrity. 我丈夫是个非常正直的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('classify', '[\'klæsɪfaɪ]', 'vt.分类；归类', '1. The books in the library are classified by subject. 图书馆的书是按科目分类的。 2. We can classify these subjects under three headings. 我们可以将这些题目加以分类成三个主题。 3. Would you classify her novels as serious literature or other? 你认为她的小说属于文学类，还是其它类? 4. It is entirly proper to classify Kant as a transcendental idealist. 把康德化归类为先验的唯心主义者是完全正确的。', '形容词: classifiable 过去式: classified 过去分词: classified 现在分词: classifying 第三人称单数: classifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ponder', '[\'pɑːndər]', 'v.沉思；考虑', '1. You should pause and ponder now. 你现在应该停下来仔细考虑一下。 2. He pondered long and deeply over the question. 他对该问题作了长时间的深思。 3. We pondered whether to tell her. 我们考虑是否要告诉她。 4. He pondered for some minutes before giving an answer. 他思考了几分钟才作答复。', '名词: ponderer 过去式: pondered 过去分词: pondered 现在分词: pondering 第三人称单数: ponders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concrete', '[\'kɑːŋkriːt]', 'adj.具体的；实质性的；混凝土的 n.水泥；混凝土；具体物 v.凝结；结合', '1. I can\'t tell you anything concrete. 这具体的我也说不上来。 2. He had nothing concrete to fasten it upon. 他抓不到什么具体的证据。 3. The statue rests on a bed of concrete. 这座雕像立在混凝土的基座上。 4. Between these are fixed precast concrete external cladding panels. 在它们之间填上预制混凝土的外层空心板。 5. Tom tumbled over and hit his head on the concrete. 汤姆摔倒，头撞到水泥地。 6. The government concreted the road over. 政府用混凝土铺路。', '副词: concretely 名词: concreteness 过去式: concreted 过去分词: concreted 现在分词: concreting 第三人称单数: concretes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('munificent', '[mjuː\'nɪfɪsnt]', 'adj.慷慨的；大方的', '1. Certainly those who spread the message of Godhead are most munificent. 的确，那些传播首神讯息的人们是最慷慨的。 2. The old man\'s munificent donation to the hospital was highly appreciated. 老人对医院慷慨的捐赠赢得了高度赞扬。', '副词: munificently 名词: munificence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scout', '[skaʊt]', 'n.童子军；侦察员；守卫 vt.侦察；物色', '1. I remember when I used to be a Girl Scout. 我记得我还是一名女童子军的时候。 2. The scout spurred on to the destination. 侦察员向目的地疾驰而去。 3. The scout was searching through the woods. 侦察员正在树林中搜索。 4. Three planes were sent up to scout. 派出三架飞机侦察。', '名词: scouter 过去式: scouted 过去分词: scouted 现在分词: scouting 第三人称单数: scouts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('salamander', '[\'sæləmændər]', 'n.蝾螈；火蜥蜴；能耐高温的物件', '1. Salamanders once were thought to be capable of living in fire. 火蜥蜴曾被认为能生活于火中。', '形容词: salamandrine');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('committee', '[kə\'mɪti]', 'n.委员会', '1. The committee meets at three today. 委员会今天三点开会。 2. Moderates have displaced the extremists on the committee. 在委员会中，稳健派人士取代了激进派人士。 3. Some members of the committee expressed reservations about the proposal. 委员会一些成员对这项提议持保留态度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('doomed', '[dʊmd]', 'adj.命中注定的 动词doom的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The project is doomed to fail. 这计划注定要失败。 2. The enterprise was doomed to failure. 该企业注定要失败。 3. He seemed doomed to live a life of poverty. 他似乎注定要过贫困的生活。 4. Why are my plans always doomed to failure? 为什么我的计划总是遭到失败?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gaze', '[ɡeɪz]', 'vi.凝视 n.凝视', '1. She sat gazing out of the window. 她坐着凝视着窗外。 2. He gaze ruefully in the mirror at his greying lock. 他凝视著镜中自己日见花白的头发，感慨岁月不待人。 3. She gazed at me in disbelief when I told her the news. 我告诉她这消息时，她以怀疑的目光注视著我。 4. Your intent gaze made her uncomfortable. 你的注目凝视使她感到不自在。', '名词: gazer 过去式: gazed 过去分词: gazed 现在分词: gazing 第三人称单数: gazes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cabinet', '[\'kæbɪnət]', 'n.橱柜；内阁 adj.内阁的；秘密的', '1. She needs a cherry cabinet in her room. 她需要在她房里添一个樱桃木的柜子。 2. I put my collection of old glasses in the cabinet. 我把收集的古玻璃器皿放在橱里。 3. The question was discussed in cabinet. 在内阁会议上讨论了这个问题。 4. They have found out the mole in the cabinet. 他们已经发现了内阁中的间谍。 5. He was elevated to cabinet rank. 他被提升到内阁部长级。', '名词: cabinetful');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ascend', '[ə\'send]', 'v.上升；攀登', '1. The stairs in the hotel ascend in a graceful curve. 这个旅店的楼梯以优美的曲线上升。 2. It is easier to descend than to ascend. 下降容易上升难。 3. A small party is planning to ascend Mount Everest. 一小伙人正计划攀登珠穆朗玛峰。 4. Setting foot on the island, he began to ascend the trail. 他踏上荒岛，开始顺着小径往上攀登。', '形容词: ascendable 过去式: ascended 过去分词: ascended 现在分词: ascending 第三人称单数: ascends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('paraphrase', '[\'pærəfreɪz]', 'n.释义；解述；改写 v.改写；解述', '1. The teacher amplified the sense by a paraphrase. 老师用转述释义的方法详述了它的意义。 2. She gave us a paraphrase of that film. 她向我们复述了那部电影。 3. The paraphrase of the sonnet is easy to understand. 该十四行诗的意译易于理解。 4. Paraphrase this article in 250 words or less. 用不到 250 个字意译出这篇文章。', '形容词: paraphrasable 名词: paraphraser 过去式: paraphrased 过去分词: paraphrased 现在分词: paraphrasing 第三人称单数: paraphrases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('untamed', '[ˌʌn\'teɪmd]', 'adj.不能抑制的；难控驭的', '1. To live a life untamed and unafraid. 活得不受拘束并无所畏惧。 2. Feral: existing in a wild or untamed state. 野性的,处于一种野性或未驯服的状态。 3. Existing in a wild or untamed state. 野性的处于一种野性或未。 4. Having returned to an untamed state from domestication. 从驯服到变野的状态的', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incongruity', '[ˌɪnkɒn\'ɡruːəti]', 'n.不调和；不一致；不配合', '1. She was struck by the incongruity of the situation. 这一局面煞是怪异，让她惊愕不已。 2. It was a night when sorrow may come to the brightest without causing any great sense of incongruity. 这是一个可由哀愁变为狂喜而又不引起任何严重不协调感的夜晚。 3. The incongruity of the word \"spirit\" in his mouth struck him so sharply. 从他嘴里说出不相称的“血气”这两个字,真是强烈地感动了他。', '名词复数: incongruities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coordinate', '[koʊ\'ɔːrdɪneɪt]', 'v.（使）协调；（使）一致；（使）同等 n.坐标；同等的人物；配套服装 adj.同等的；等位的；(大学)男女分院制的', '1. You must coordinate the movements of your arms and legs when swimming. 游泳时你必须使臂和腿的动作相协调。 2. If we coordinate our efforts we should be able to win the game. 如果我们同心协力,我们应该能够打赢这场比赛。 3. You must coordinate what you said with what you did. 你必须使你的言行一致。 4. The filter is defined as a box of coordinates. 过滤器定义的是一个方框的坐标。 5. This coordinate system is called the triad at the point. 这个坐标系叫做该点的三面形坐标系。', '形容词: coordinative 副词: coordinately 名词: coordinateness 过去式: coordinated 过去分词: coordinated 现在分词: coordinating 第三人称单数: coordinates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concept', '[\'kɑːnsept]', 'n.观念；概念；想法', '1. I can not understand such an abstract concept. 我无法理解如此抽象的观念。 2. He presented a new concept of the origins of the universe. 他提出了一种宇宙起源的新概念。 3. We had no concept that this tiny mistake would ruin the whole plan. 我们完全没有想到这个小小的失误会毁掉整个计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emerald', '[\'emərəld]', 'n.翡翠；绿宝石；翡翠绿 adj.翡翠的；翠绿色的', '1. May\'s birthstone is the emerald. 五月的诞生石是翡翠。 2. Evening settles in over Emerald Lake in Yoho National Park. 夜幕降临在育空国家公园的翡翠湖上。 3. She is wearing a ring set with emerald. 她戴著一枚嵌有绿宝石的戒指。 4. Jiuzhaigou is just like an emerald. 九寨沟就像一颗绿宝石。 5. Her jaw line tightened to squareness and her eyes went emerald. 她的下颚紧得成了方形，她的眼睛变成翡翠的颜色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convention', '[kən\'venʃn]', 'n.大会；协定；惯例；公约', '1. The convention looms as political battle. 这场大会将是一场政治角斗。 2. Delegates will be picked at a convention. 代表将在大会上选出。 3. This convention results in no ambiguity. 这个协定不会导致误解。 4. The countries all agreed to sign the convention. 各国都同意签署这项协定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('literature', '[\'lɪtrətʃər]', 'n.文学；文献；<口>印刷品', '1. She is fond of polite literature. 她喜爱风雅文学。 2. He destroyed feudal ideas in literature. 他摧毁了文学中的封建思想。 3. The principal literature comes from zoology. 主要文献都来自动物学。 4. Beijing was first named ji in literature. 北京最早见于文献的名称叫做蓟。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('statistic', '[stə\'tɪstɪk]', 'n.统计数值', '1. The statistics were given in parenthesis. 统计数字在括号里。 2. I happen to have the official statistics with me. 我碰巧身边有官方的统计数字。 3. Have you any statistics that would enforce your argument? 你有任何统计资料可以加强你的论点吗？ 4. These are some indigestible statistics. 这是些很难理解的统计资料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('migrate', '[\'maɪɡreɪt]', 'vi.迁移；迁徙；转移', '1. These workers migrate from country to country in search of work. 这些工人为寻找工作从一个国家迁移到另一个国家。 2. Some tribes migrate with their cattle in search of fresh grass. 有些部落为了寻找新鲜的牧草而带着他们的牲畜迁移。 3. In some developing countries more and more people migrate to urban area. 在某些发展中的国家，越来越多的人向市区迁移。 4. Large numbers of birds migrate south every winter. 每年冬季大量的鸟类迁徙南方。', '名词: migrator 过去式: migrated 过去分词: migrated 现在分词: migrating 第三人称单数: migrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('visual', '[\'vɪʒuəl]', 'adj.视觉的；视力的；看的见的；形象的 n.画面；图象', '1. Her designs have a strong visual appeal. 她的设计在视觉上很有感染力。 2. He has a good visual memory. 他有良好的视觉记忆力。 3. His failed to pass his visual test. 他没有通过他的视力测试。', '副词: visually 名词: visualness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diagnosis', '[ˌdaɪəɡ\'noʊsɪs]', 'n.诊断；调查分析', '1. The two doctors made different diagnosis of my disease. 两位医生对我的病作出了不同的诊断。 2. We waited in great suspense for the doctor\'s diagnosis. 我们焦急万分地等候医生做出诊断。 3. A positive diagnosis can be made only after ruling out gastric and duodenal ulcer. 只有排除了胃溃疡和十二指肠溃疡的可能性之后，才能作出明确诊断。 4. The engineer made a complete diagnosis of the bridge\'s collapse. 工程师对桥的倒塌做一次彻底的调查分析。', '名词复数: diagnoses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('determine', '[dɪ\'tɜːrmɪn]', 'v.决定；决心；确定；测定', '1. Chance will determine the outcome. 机缘将决定结果 2. I must now determine whether to meet him or not. 我现在必须决定是否要见他。 3. I am determined to find out the rights and wrongs of this matter. 我决心查明这件事的真相。 4. An inquest was held to determine the cause of his death. 为确定他的死因进行了审问。', '过去式: determined 过去分词: determined 现在分词: determining 第三人称单数: determines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aperture', '[\'æpətʃər]', 'n.孔；孔径；光圈；缝隙', '1. We saw light through a small aperture in the wall. 我们透过墙上的小孔看到了亮光。 2. The only light came through a narrow aperture. 仅有的光来自一个小孔。 3. Into this aperture a droplet of mercury was poured. 一小滴水银滴进了这个小孔。 4. He stopped down the lens to a small aperture. 他把镜头光圈孔径缩小。', '形容词: apertural');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gratitude', '[\'ɡrætɪtuːd]', 'n.感激；感谢；感恩', '1. His heart overflowed with gratitude. 他的心里充满了感激之情。 2. She showed me her gratitude by inviting me to dinner. 她邀请我吃饭以表示她的感激。 3. We welcome the opportunity to express our gratitude. 我们能有机会表示谢意十分高兴。 4. We owe you a debt of gratitude for you help. 承蒙帮助，感恩不尽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clumsy', '[\'klʌmzi]', 'adj.笨拙的；不得体的；笨重的', '1. The clumsy boy bumped into the table. 笨拙的男孩撞到桌子上。 2. My clumsy answer hurt her feelings. 我笨拙的回答伤了她的感情。 3. He chided his son for being clumsy. 他斥责儿子笨手笨脚。 4. This cobbler is rather clumsy. 这个补鞋匠真是笨手笨脚。', '副词: clumsily 比较级: clumsier 最高级: clumsiest 名词: clumsiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apologize', '[ə\'pɑːlədʒaɪz]', 'vi.道歉；赔罪', '1. He apologizes to her for not going to her party. 他因未出席她的派对向她表示歉意。 2. I apologize if I hurt your feelings. 如果我伤害了你的感情,那我道歉。 3. You must apologize to him for your fault. 你必须为你的过失向他赔罪。', '名词: apologizer 过去式: apologized 过去分词: apologized 现在分词: apologizing 第三人称单数: apologizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imprisonment', '[ɪm\'prɪznmənt]', 'n.【U】监禁；关押；禁锢', '1. For an offence of this gravity, imprisonment is the usual punishment. 对这种重大罪行通常处以监禁。 2. Serious crime must be punished by longer terms of imprisonment. 重罪须处以长期监禁。 3. He got two years\' imprisonment for assaulting a police officer. 他因袭击警察而遭两年监禁。 4. Recent events lean me more towards favoring longer years of imprisonment. 最近发生的事件更使我倾向于延长罪犯关押年限的意见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commander', '[kə\'mændər]', 'n.司令官；指挥官', '1. The commander ordered a counterattack. 司令官命令反攻。 2. Commander Rahm arrives, swinging a swagger stick. 拉姆司令官挥舞着一柄短手杖来到了。 3. The army was arrayed before the commander. 部队在指挥官前列好阵势。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relapse', '[rɪ\'læps]', 'v.复发；再陷入；故态复萌 n.再发；重陷；故态复萌', '1. Some patients will relapse. 一些患者会复发。 2. We were afraid he might relapse into a coma. 我们担心他可能再次陷入昏迷。 3. He had relapsed into silence again. 他再一次陷入沉默。 4. He kept off drink for a few weeks, but now he has relapsed. 他酒戒了两三个星期，可是现在故态复萌。 5. He can\'t return to work because he\'s had a relapse. 他不能回去工作，因为旧病复发了。', '名词: relapser 过去式: relapsed 过去分词: relapsed 现在分词: relapsing 第三人称单数: relapses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extinguish', '[ɪk\'stɪŋɡwɪʃ]', 'vt.熄灭；扑灭；消灭；使破灭；偿清', '1. Smoking is forbidden. Please extinguish your cigarettes. 吸烟是禁止的，请你把烟熄掉。 2. They tried to extinguish the flames. 他们竭力要把火焰扑灭。 3. The dictator wanted to extinguish all of his opposition in one go. 这位独裁者想一口气消灭所有对手。 4. Nothing could extinguish his faith in human nature. 没有什么能使他丧失对人性的信心。', '形容词: extinguishable 名词: extinguishment 过去式: extinguished 过去分词: extinguished 现在分词: extinguishing 第三人称单数: extinguishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('random', '[\'rændəm]', 'adj.任意的；随机的；随意的 n.随意；任意 adv.随机地', '1. Men are exposed to more acts of random physical violence. 男人受到更多的任意的身体强烈活动。 2. Most people know that the outcome of a coin toss is random. 大部分人都知道掷硬币的结果是随机的。 3. The computer will generate apparently random numbers. 电脑似乎将随机产生号码。 4. This random approach is not as dubious as one might expect. 这种随意的途径并不象人们所预期的那样无把握。 5. Soiled dishes were piled at random. 脏碟子胡乱地堆放着。 6. Complex organs made up of separate but necessary subsystems cannot be the result of random chance. 复杂的器官是由独立的，必要的子系统组成，而且不能随机地形成。', '副词: randomly 名词: randomness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outcome', '[\'aʊtkʌm]', 'n.结果；后果', '1. What was the outcome of your meeting? 你们会晤的结果如何? 2. The outcome of the election is a foregone conclusion. 选举结果已在预料之中。 3. The outcome of the game is beyond his fondest hopes. 比赛结果使他大喜过望。 4. Public interest centres on the outcome of next week\'s by-election. 公众的注意力集中在下周的补选结果上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('undertake', '[ˌʌndər\'teɪk]', 'v.承担；从事；保证；答应', '1. We could undertake the work for the time being. 我们可暂时承担这项工作。 2. We shall undertake the construction of this bridge. 我们将负责这座桥的修建工程。 3. Whatever I may undertake in the coming years, I don\'t need your help. 未来无论我从事什么,我都不需要你的帮助。 4. I can not undertake that you will make a profit. 我不能保证你会获利。', '过去式: undertook 过去分词: undertaken 现在分词: undertaking 第三人称单数: undertakes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hustle', '[\'hʌsl]', 'v.催促；赶紧做；推搡；<俚>(不正当)买卖；欺诈 n.忙乱；推搡；<俚>欺诈行为', '1. The mother hustled the children off to school and started working. 母亲打发孩子们赶快去上学，然后就开始干起活来。 2. He hustled into and out of the office. 他急匆匆地走进办公室，又匆匆离去了。 3. The thief was hustled off to gaol. 那窃贼被推推搡搡进入监房。 4. He hustled him out of his savings. 他把他的储蓄骗走了。 5. It seems that he enjoys the hustle and bustle of life in the big city. 看起来他似乎很喜欢大城市的热闹繁忙的生活。', '名词: hustler 过去式: hustled 过去分词: hustled 现在分词: hustling 第三人称单数: hustles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('block', '[blɑːk]', 'n.街区；木块；石块；大楼；一组；阻塞(物)；障碍(物) v.阻塞', '1. Walk two blocks down the street and go past the city hall. 顺这条街走两个街区，过市政厅。 2. The doctors succeeded in confining the contagious disease within the block. 医生们成功地将这个传染病控制在这一街区的范围内。 3. The floor was made of wooden blocks. 地板是用木块拼成的。 4. The blocks should be laid on a bed of concrete. 石块应该固定在混凝土基座上。', '名词: blocker 过去式: blocked 过去分词: blocked 现在分词: blocking 第三人称单数: blocks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('afford', '[ə\'fɔːrd]', 'v.花费得起；能够做；承担得起(后果)；提供；给予', '1. Only the well-to-do can afford these houses. 只有富人能买得起这些房子。 2. I can\'t afford a holiday this summer. 今年夏天我无法度假。 3. We can afford to overlook minor offences. 我们可以不计较小过。 4. We can\'t afford to pay such a price. 我们付不起这个价钱。', '过去式: afforded 过去分词: afforded 现在分词: affording 第三人称单数: affords');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('analysis', '[ə\'næləsɪs]', 'n.分析；解析', '1. His analysis of the problem showed great perception. 他对该问题的分析显示出敏锐的洞察力。 2. We agreed with his acute analysis of the political situation. 我们都同意他对政治形势的深刻分析。 3. Close analysis of sales figures showed clear regional variations. 对销售额的仔细分析显示出明显的地区差别。 4. In the final analysis I think our sympathy lies with the heroine of the play. 总之，我们认为我们都同情剧中的女主人公。', '名词复数: analyses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insufficient', '[ˌɪnsə\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.不足的', '1. The food was insufficient for our needs. 食物不够我们的需要。 2. I felt my knowledge was insufficient. 我感到知识不足。 3. There is insufficient light for reading. 这里光线不足,不适合阅读。 4. His children were dwarfed by insufficient food. 他的儿女因营养不良而发育不全。', '副词: insufficiently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('colony', '[\'kɑːləni]', 'n.殖民地；侨居地；侨民；聚居(地)；群体；菌落', '1. This country used to be a British colony in Asia. 这个国家曾是英国在亚洲的殖民地。 2. Britain was mandated to govern the former colony of German East Africa. 英国授权代管德国在东非的前殖民地。 3. That first winter in America was very hard for the new colony. 对于新侨民来说,在美国的第一个冬天是非常难熬的。 4. They live in an artists\' colony. 他们住在艺术家聚居区。', '名词复数: colonies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('company', '[\'kʌmpəni]', 'n.公司；商号；陪伴；同伴；客人；[军]连；一群 v.陪伴', '1. I work in a small company. 我在一家小公司工作。 2. The company doubled its size in nine years. 9年来这家公司的规模扩大了一倍。 3. The company has connections with a number of Japanese firms. 这家公司与几家日本商号有业务往来。 4. Don\'t mention it. I\'ve really enjoyed your company. 不必客气,有你的陪伴,我也很开心。 5. May fair winds company your safe return. 愿和风伴你平安归来。', '名词复数: companies 过去式: companied 过去分词: companied 现在分词: companying 第三人称单数: companies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discretion', '[dɪ\'skreʃn]', 'n.谨慎；慎重；自行决定', '1. We reposed great trust in his tact and discretion. 我们极为信任他的机智和谨慎。 2. You must choose you friends with discretion. 你一定要慎重地择友。 3. I won\'t tell you what time to leave, you\'re old enough to use your own discretion. 我不告诉你什么时候离开，你已经长大了，该自己作出决定。 4. The hours of the meetings will be fixed at the monitor\'s discretion. 开会时间将由班长自行决定。', '形容词: discretional 副词: discretionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impersonal', '[ɪm\'pɜːrsənl]', 'adj.不受个人感情影响的；冷淡的；没有人情味的；非特指某一人的；客观的', '1. I hate dealingwith large impersonal companies. 我讨厌与那些没有人情味的大公司打交道。 2. We indulge in riddles, rather than in the impersonal geometries that govern the day-lit world. 我们沉溺这些谜中，而不是那统治着白昼世界的没有人情味的几何。 3. He made an impersonal comment on the incident. 他对那一事件作了客观的评论。 4. They are used in impersonal and official situations. 这两个词均用於客观的及公事的场合。', '副词: impersonally 名词: impersonality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('favored', '[\'feɪvəd]', 'adj.受到优待的；赋予特殊条件的；样貌特殊的；喜欢的 =favored. 动词favor的过去式和过去分词.', '1. We decided to give favored treatment to him. 我们决定给他优待。 2. She is more advantaged than her cousin,born into the favored classes. 她比她的堂妹受优待 3. In summertime, Hokkaido is a favored refuge from the heat. 在夏季，北海道是避署的好地方。 4. Their house is in very favored position near the park. 他们的房子在公园附近一个很惬意的地段。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crab', '[kræb]', 'n.蟹；阴虱；爱争吵的人；[植]山楂子 v.捕蟹；使横行；批评；抱怨', '1. All the shops on the seafront had crab for sale. 海滨地区的全部商店都出售蟹。 2. A crab was left stranded on the beach when the tide ebbed. 退潮时，一只蟹被困留在沙滩上。 3. My neighbor is such an old crab. 我的邻居可真是个爱争吵的人。', '名词: crabber 过去式: crabbed 过去分词: crabbed 现在分词: crabbing 第三人称单数: crabs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brace', '[breɪs]', 'v.防备；支撑；绷紧；振作 n.支柱；支架；牙箍；一对；（复）吊带裤；大括号', '1. It is urgent that we brace against hurricanes. 我们必须做好防飓风的准备。 2. The struts are firmly braced. 那些支柱上得很牢固。 3. She braced herself against the wall. 她靠在墙上。 4. He faced the angry crowd, his arms folded, his legs braced. 面对着愤怒的人群,他抱紧双臂,绷紧双腿。 5. The odor of souls is a brace to the walls. 灵魂的气息是这些砖墙的支柱。', '过去式: braced 过去分词: braced 现在分词: bracing 第三人称单数: braces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('berate', '[bɪ\'reɪt]', 'v.〈正式或文〉严厉责备', '1. But to ban them and berate them seems doubly dippy. 但是禁止或者严厉指着他们看起来是不理智的。 2. He frowned and was about to berate her. 他皱着眉头,刚刚想要责备她。 3. To scold or rebuke sharply;berate. 痛骂，斥责；责备 4. To scold or rebuke sharply; berate. 痛骂，斥责；责备', '过去式: berated 过去分词: berated 现在分词: berating 第三人称单数: berates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('biography', '[baɪ\'ɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.传记', '1. He likes to read biographies of great men to promote himself. 他喜欢读伟人传记来提高自己。 2. His biography is a saga of scientific research. 他的传记就是一部科研记实。 3. I have read a biography of Abraham Lincoln. 我读过一部亚伯拉罕•林肯的传记。', '名词复数: biographies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gauche', '[ɡoʊʃ]', 'adj.笨拙的；粗鲁的；不善交际的', '1. He now seems gauche and uninteresting. 他显得又笨拙又古板。 2. He\'s rather gauche; he hasn\'t found his feet socially yet. 他蛮笨拙的,到现在还找不到在这社会上的立足之地。 3. I find him terribly gauche. 我认为他太不圆通了。', '副词: gauchely 名词: gaucheness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chronic', '[\'krɑːnɪk]', 'adj.长期的；慢性的；惯常的', '1. There is a chronic unemployment problem in America. 在美国存在长期失业问题。 2. We finally won in this chronic war. 我们终于打赢了这场长期战争。 3. My brother has chronic bronchitis. 我的哥哥患有慢性支气管炎。 4. Have you got any chronic diseases in the past? 你过去有没有慢性病?', '副词: chronically 名词: chronicity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suspicious', '[sə\'spɪʃəs]', 'adj.可疑的；多疑的', '1. I am suspicious of his intentions. 我怀疑他的用意。 2. Two suspicious characters were brought in. 逮捕了两名嫌疑犯。 3. I feel suspicious about the truth of the account. 我对于这帐目的真实性感到怀疑。 4. The locals tend to be suspicious of strangers. 当地人对陌生人往往有戒心。', '副词: suspiciously 名词: suspiciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hail', '[heɪl]', 'n.冰雹 vi.下冰雹 vt.招呼；喝彩；宣称；来自 n.欢呼', '1. For three hours, the hail rattles on the roof. 一连三个小时，冰雹在屋顶上哗啦哗啦地下着。 2. The hail beat a loud tattoo on the windowpane. 冰雹在窗玻璃上嘈杂地连续敲打。 3. It\'s hailing outside. 外面在下冰雹。 4. An old friend hailed me from the other side of the street. 一个老朋友从街的对面喊我。 5. The youngsters greeted their idol with a hail. 那群年轻人向他们的偶像欢呼致敬。', '过去式: hailed 过去分词: hailed 现在分词: hailing 第三人称单数: hails');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coax', '[koʊks]', 'v.哄；诱骗；灵巧慢慢地做', '1. The clerk is always able to coax the customers into good humor. 那个售货员总是能够把顾客哄得高高兴兴的。 2. Mother ran after me, murmuring fine words to coax me. 母亲在后面小跑着，嘴里还在不断地说着好话哄我。 3. I\'ve come back to coax a respectable sum of money out of an aged woman who happens also to be my mother. 我回来的目的，是从一个老太婆手上诱骗一笔数目可观的金钱，她碰巧是我母亲。', '副词: coaxingly 名词: coaxer 过去式: coaxed 过去分词: coaxed 现在分词: coaxing 第三人称单数: coaxes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('breeze', '[briːz]', 'n.微风；<口>轻而易举的事；焦炭渣 v.飘然而行；轻松通过', '1. The wheat rippled in the breeze. 小麦在微风中起伏波动。 2. We are enjoying the cool breeze that comes from the lake. 我们享受着湖面上吹来的凉爽微风。 3. We got the job done in a breeze. 我们轻而易举就把这件事办了。 4. Teaching you English is by no means a breeze. 教你英语绝对不是什么轻而易举的事。 5. She breezed along, smiling at everyone. 她轻盈地向前走去，对每个人都嫣然含笑。', '过去式: breezed 过去分词: breezed 现在分词: breezing 第三人称单数: breezes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gainful', '[\'ɡeɪnfl]', 'adj.有利益的；有报酬的；唯利是图的', '1. Are you in gainful employment? 你有报酬的工作吗?', '副词: gainfully 名词: gainfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('predominate', '[prɪ\'dɑːmɪneɪt]', 'v.占优势；支配', '1. Conservatives might predominate in the government. 保守派人士有可能在政府中占优势。 2. Pine trees predominate the woods here. 这儿的树林中最多的是松树。 3. Red and scarlet predominate in these flowers. 这些花中大都是红色和鲜红色的。 4. He soon began to predominate over them. 他不久就开始支配他们了。', '副词: predominately 名词: predomination 过去式: predominated 过去分词: predominated 现在分词: predominating 第三人称单数: predominates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preeminent', '[priː\'emɪnənt]', 'adj.卓越的；优秀的；超群的', '1. His preeminent services had entitled him to the first place in his country\'s love. 他卓越的功绩，使得他最为全国人民所爱戴。 2. This country has always been preeminent in the field of medical research. 这个国家在医学研究领域上一直是卓越超群的。', '副词: preeminently 异体字: pre-eminent 名词: preeminence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('patronizing', '[\'peɪtrənaɪzɪŋ]', 'adj.以恩人自居的；居高临下的 动词patronize的现在分词形式.', '1. His manner, if patronizing, was not unkind. 他的态度即使有点傲慢，也不能说是不和善。 2. Where does she get off patronizing me like that? 她以为她是谁啊?竟然如此居高临下地跟我说话!', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concur', '[kən\'kɜːr]', 'v.意见相同；同时发生', '1. I concur with him in many points. 我和他在许多论点上意见是一致的。 2. Did all the members concur in getting a bank loan? 委员们是否都同意向银行贷款。 3. She has expressed her opposition to the plan, and I fully concur . 她对计划表示反对 4. Wealth and happiness do not always concur. 财富与幸福并非总是并存的。', '过去式: concurred 过去分词: concurred 现在分词: concurring 第三人称单数: concurs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('journal', '[\'dʒɜːrnl]', 'n.日志；日记；期刊', '1. He kept a journal during his visit to Japan. 他在访问日本期间坚持记日记。 2. He wrote a journal of his travels. 他写了一本旅行日记。 3. He subscribed to a journal this year. 今年他订了一份期刊。 4. The journal makes its appearance once two months. 这本刊物两个月出版一次。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brush', '[brʌʃ]', 'n.刷子；画笔；刷 n.灌木丛 n.小冲突；争吵 vt.刷；掠过；轻触；擦；掸 vi.轻擦；拂拭', '1. He painted the wall with a brush. 他用刷子涂墙。 2. The painter swept a brush over his canvas. 画家的画笔在画布上飞掠。 3. I\'ll give my coat a good brush. 我要把我的衣服好好刷一下。 4. Let\'s burn off the rest of the brush. 让我们把剩下的灌木丛清除掉。 5. He had a brush with his neighbour. 他和邻居发生了一点摩擦。 6. We should brush our teeth at least twice a day. 我们每天应该至少刷两次牙。 7. Don\'t bother to move.I think I can just brush past. 不必麻烦动了,我想我能擦身挤过去。', '形容词: brushy 名词: brusher 过去式: brushed 过去分词: brushed 现在分词: brushing 第三人称单数: brushes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mysterious', '[mɪ\'stɪriəs]', 'adj.神秘的；不可思议的', '1. The enchanter is very mysterious. 魔法师非常神秘。 2. Africa is a mysterious land to him. 对他来说，非洲是一片神秘的土地。 3. We must pay special attention to the mysterious stranger. 我们必须对那个神秘的陌生人严加注意。 4. There are many mysterious stories about the Egyptian pyramids. 关于埃及金字塔有许多神秘的故事。', '副词: mysteriously 名词: mysteriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maintenance', '[\'meɪntənəns]', 'n.维修；维护；保持；生活费用；抚养费', '1. He\'s taking classes in car maintenance. 他正在上汽车维修课。 2. The machinery requires constant maintenance. 这些机器需要经常保养维修。 3. The roof of the ancient temple caved in because of bad maintenance. 那座古老的宙宇由于维护不好屋顶塌了下来。 4. Our policy is maintenance of friendly relations with all countries. 我们的政策是与所有国家保持友好关系。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plea', '[pliː]', 'n.恳求；申诉；抗辩；借口', '1. The prisoner made a plea for mercy. 囚犯恳求宽恕。 2. She made an impassioned plea for justice. 她激昂地抗辩，恳求获得公正。 3. In making that plea he will breathe in vain. 他做那种恳求是白费口舌的。 4. The thief entered a plea of not guilty. 这个贼提出了无罪申诉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anonymous', '[ə\'nɑːnɪməs]', 'adj.匿名的；无名的；没特色的', '1. It is unpleasant to receive anonymous letters. 接到匿名信是一件令人不快的事。 2. The man was arrested after an anonymous tip-off. 有人匿名举报后，那个人被抓了起来。 3. The author chooses to remain anonymous. 作者愿不署名。 4. An anonymous author wrote this book. 这本书出自无名氏之手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('triumph', '[\'traɪʌmf]', 'n.凯旋；成就；胜利；欢欣 vi.战胜；庆祝胜利', '1. The winning team returned home in triumph. 球队凯旋而归。 2. The bridge is a triumph of modern engineering. 这座桥是现代工程的一大成就。 3. A smile of triumph lit up her face. 她的脸上闪露出胜利的微笑。 4. We finally won a diplomatic triumph. 我们终于赢得了外交的胜利。 5. Advancing culture is bound to triumph over declining culture. 先进的文化必然战胜没落的文化。', '过去式: triumphed 过去分词: triumphed 现在分词: triumphing 第三人称单数: triumphs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sweat', '[swet]', 'n.汗水 n.焦急；繁重工作；(凝结在物体表面的)水珠 v.(使)出汗', '1. He is covered with sweat. 他浑身是汗。 2. Camel, soaked with sweat, makes a hand expression for \"shush\" secretly. 满身大汗的卡梅尔悄悄地做出一个“嘘”的手势。 3. She stood up to wipe the sweat off her face. 她站起来擦擦脸上的汗珠。 4. Sweat was pouring down his face. 他满头大汗。 5. I was all of a sweat before the exam. 我临考前急得不得了. 6. The long climb made us sweat. 我们攀登了很长距离，已大汗淋漓了。', '过去式: sweated/sweat 过去分词: sweated/sweat 现在分词: sweating 第三人称单数: sweats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obliging', '[ə\'blaɪdʒɪŋ]', 'adj.乐于助人的 动词oblige的现在分词.', '1. He is a very obliging, amiable person. 他是一个非常乐于助人的和蔼可亲的人。 2. They were very obliging and offered to wait for us. 他们非常热情，主动提出等候我们。', '副词: obligingly 名词: obligingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lobby', '[\'lɑːbi]', 'n.大厅；民众接待厅；游说议员者 v.游说', '1. I waited for her in the lobby of theatre yesterday. 昨天我在戏院的大厅等她。 2. The film star held court in the hotel lobby. 这位电影明星在旅馆的大厅里接见了影迷。 3. The anti-nuclear lobby is becoming stronger. 向议员游说的反核群众声势渐强。 4. The group tried to lobby the bill through. 这个集团企图通过游说议员通过该项法案。', '名词: lobbyer 名词复数: lobbies 过去式: lobbied 过去分词: lobbied 现在分词: lobbying 第三人称单数: lobbies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preclude', '[prɪ\'kluːd]', 'vt.阻止；排除', '1. That will preclude him from escaping. 那将阻止他逃走，那将使他无法逃走。 2. Their move does not preclude others from investing. 他们这一行动并不影响其他人进行投资。 3. My present finances preclude the possibility of buying a car. 按我目前的财务状况我是不可能买车的。 4. Small volume this year does not preclude huge volume next year. 今年业绩不多，不代表明年就一定会很少，', '形容词: preclusive 副词: preclusively 名词: preclusion 过去式: precluded 过去分词: precluded 现在分词: precluding 第三人称单数: precludes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('collect', '[kə\'lekt]', 'v.收集；聚集；募捐；运走；使（自己）镇定', '1. He used to collect cards, but now he likes to collect stamps. 他以前收集卡片,现在却喜欢收集邮票。 2. A crowd soon collected at the scene of the accident. 群众迅速聚集在出事现场。 3. He\'s collecting (money) for famine relief. 他正在为赈济饥民募捐. 4. The dustmen collect the rubbish once a week. 垃圾工每周运走一次垃圾.', '过去式: collected 过去分词: collected 现在分词: collecting 第三人称单数: collects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('moral', '[\'mɔːrəl]', 'adj.道德的；精神上的 n.寓意；道德；品行；伦理', '1. She regards his moral faults with charity. 她宽恕他的品行不端。 2. We differ about moral standards. 我们对道德标准看法不一致。 3. His behavior transgressed the moral rules of the social conduct. 他的行为违背了社会行为的道德准则。 4. It comprises two main sets of rights: the economic rights and the moral rights. 版权包括两种主要的权利:经济权利和精神权利。 5. The moral of this story is ‘Better late than never\'. 这个故事的寓意是｀迟做总比不做好＇.', '副词: morally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('healing', '[\'hiːlɪŋ]', 'n.康复；复原 adj.有治疗功用的 动词heal的现在分词.', '1. I saw my acupuncturist weekly and the healing process accelerated. 我每周见一次我的针灸医生，康复的进度加快了。 2. So you don\'t wanna negate medicine, every form of healing has a place. 所以你不是要去拒绝药物;每一种康复方法都有它自己存在的理由。 3. This salve will assist healing of the wound. 这种药膏能促进伤口的愈合。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('saving', '[\'seɪvɪŋ]', 'n. 节约； 挽救 （复数)savings:储蓄金； 存款 prep. 除 ... 之外 conj. 除了； 除去 save的现在分词', '1. A saving of 30% is obtainable under this scheme. 按这一计划做可以获得百分之三十的节约率。 2. We must work out a better method of saving paper. 我们必须想出更好的节约纸张的方法。 3. They have thought out the effective saving. 他们已想出挽救的办法。 4. He took the chance of losing his life in saving the drowning child. 他冒着生命危险去挽救那个落入水中的小孩。 5. I would like to open a saving account. 我想开活期存款户。 6. It was debated whether saving grace could be obtained outside the membership of the church. 人们在争论除了加入教会之外还有没有其它好处。 7. Apart from saving you time, it also brings in a world of information and knowledge and acquaints you with the latest happenings in your fields of interest. 除了能够为你节省时间，它也能将你带入到一个信息和知识的世界，它能让你接触到你所感兴趣领域里最新的信息。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complimentary', '[ˌkɑːmplɪ\'mentri]', 'adj.问候的；称赞的；免费赠送的', '1. My boss was very complimentary about my work. 老板对我的工作极其称赞。 2. She was highly complimentary about my paintings. 她对我的画给予了高度评价. 3. My boss was very complimentary about my work. 老板对我的工作极其称赞。 4. Don\'t be fooled by all his complimentary remarks they were all said with tongue in cheek. 别让他的恭维话给糊弄住--那些话可当不得真。', '副词: complimentarily');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gauge', '[ɡeɪdʒ]', 'n.测量仪器；测量标准；（铁道的）轨距；（钢丝等的）直径；（枪管的）口径 v.估计；判断；测量', '1. The fuel gauges dropped swiftly. 燃料表指针迅速下降。 2. What gauge of wire should we use for this job? 我们干这活应该用多大号的铅丝? 3. This is a narrow-gauge railway. 这是一条窄轨铁路。 4. We must gauge the diameter of wire first. 我们必须先测量电线的直径。 5. It was difficult to gauge how people would respond. 大家的反应如何难以估计。', '形容词: gaugeable 过去式: gauged/gaged 过去分词: gauged/gaged 现在分词: gauging/gaging 第三人称单数: gauges/gages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hatch', '[hætʃ]', 'n.孵化；舱口，舱口盖 v.孵；孵出；策划', '1. The hatch date for tit eggs appears to be determined about a month earlier, when the eggs are laid. 白颊山雀孵化的时间，似乎在孵化前一个月，也就是下蛋时便已决定。 2. Both men quickly disappeared down the hatch. 两个人很快从舱口下去不见了。 3. We heard the noise of a hatch being closed. 我们听到关舱口的声音。 4. An incubator is used to hatch chicken. 孵卵器用来孵小鸡。', '名词: hatcher 过去式: hatched 过去分词: hatched 现在分词: hatching 第三人称单数: hatches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reef', '[riːf]', 'n.暗礁；矿脉 n.缩帆部 v.缩帆；卷起', '1. The ship was wrecked on a reef. 这船触礁失事了。 2. Our ship was able to haul up just before it hit the submerged reef. 我们的船就在要撞上暗礁的时候停住了。 3. The ship struck a hidden reef and went dawn with all hands. 船只撞上暗礁与全体船员一起沉没。 4. The captain ordered to reef the sails for docking. 船长下令收帆以靠港。', '形容词: reefy 过去式: reefed 过去分词: reefed 现在分词: reefing 第三人称单数: reefs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amiable', '[\'eɪmiəbl]', 'adj.和蔼的；亲切的', '1. The amiable countenance of Mr. Pickwick was fast recovering its customary expression. 匹克威克先生的和蔼的脸孔在很快地恢复着平常的表情。 2. The hostess received her friends with an amiable smile. 女主人带着亲切的微笑迎接朋友们的到来。 3. You can sort out any differences you have in an amiable manner. 你可以以温柔亲切的主式澄清所有的误会。', '副词: amiably 名词: amiability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defile', '[dɪ\'faɪl]', 'vt.弄脏；污损；败坏；玷污 vi.以纵队前进 n.(山间)小道；狭谷', '1. Who are these men who defile the grassy borders of our roads and lanes. 是谁污损了我们大路和小路两旁的草坪。 2. Insults alone cannot defile a person\'s honour. 仅靠辱骂不可能败坏一个人的名誉。 3. Do not defile yourselves by any of these things. 在这一切的事上，你们都不可玷污自己。 4. Then the people of Israel will no longer stray from me, nor will they defile themselves anymore with all their sins. 好使以色列家不再走迷离开我，不再因各样的罪过玷污自己，只要作我的子民，我作他们的神。', '副词: defilingly 名词: defilement 过去式: defiled 过去分词: defiled 现在分词: defiling 第三人称单数: defiles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constituent', '[kən\'stʃuənt]', 'n.成分；选民；构成物 adj.构成的；组织的；立宪的', '1. Do you know the constituents of the mixture? 你知道这种混合物的成分吗？ 2. Punctuality is an important constituent of good character. 准时是优良品格的一个重要成分。 3. Last week, a constituent contacted me and asked me to help him construe an article contained within the constitution. 上星期，一位选民跟我联系，让我帮他解释一下宪法中包含的某则条款。 4. The chemical dissolves into its constituent parts when heated. 该化学药剂加热时会分解成其组成的分子。', '副词: constituently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('salient', '[\'seɪliənt]', 'adj.突出的；显著的；跳跃的 n.突出部分', '1. The salient point of his plan is summed up in this report. 他的计划的要点在这个报告中酌此概括。 2. Honesty is his most salient characteristic. 诚实是他最显著的特点。 3. She pointed out all the salient feature of the building. 她指出了该建筑物的全部显著特征。 4. The Germans withdrew to the partly prepared Hagen line at the base of the salient. 德国的部分军队已经撤到哈根防线。', '副词: saliently 名词: salientness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gentry', '[\'dʒentri]', 'n.绅士；名流；贵族们', '1. The English gentry is next below the nobility. 英国绅士的地位仅次于贵族。 2. The peasants\' revolt disturbed the gentry\'s sweet dreams. 农民在乡里造反，搅动了绅士们的酣梦。 3. In the Eighteenth Century, the clergy, like the nobility and gentry, often rode to hounds. 在18世纪，神职人员跟贵族和上流社会人士一样，常常骑马打猎。 4. In old society, the gentry lived in luxury. 在旧社会，贵族们生活奢侈。', '名词复数: gentries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('uphold', '[ʌp\'hoʊld]', 'v.支持；维护；维持；举起', '1. Eight columns uphold the big dome. 八根柱子支撑着这个大圆顶。 2. The President swore to uphold the constitution. 总统宣誓维护宪法。 3. He proffered to uphold justice. 他表示愿意维护正义。 4. The judge upheld the lower court\'s decision. 法官维持初级法院的判决。', '名词: upholder 过去式: upheld 过去分词: upheld 现在分词: upholding 第三人称单数: upholds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enormous', '[ɪ\'nɔːrməs]', 'adj.巨大的；庞大的', '1. Long ago enormous animals lived on the earth. 很久以前，地球上生活着巨大的动物。 2. She stood alone on the enormous stage. 她孤零零地站在巨大的舞台上。 3. They overlooked the enormous risks involved. 他们忽略了暗含的巨大危险。 4. The sight of such an enormous crowd astonished us. 看到如此庞大的人群我惊讶万分。', '副词: enormously 名词: enormousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('counseling', '[\'kaʊnsəlɪŋ]', 'n.顾问服务', '1. Each side of a case in court has its own counsel. 法庭上原告和被告双方都有各自的律师。 2. Credit counseling helped us get out from under. 信用咨询使我们免除了忧虑', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distress', '[dɪ\'stres]', 'n.不幸；危难；苦恼；痛苦 vt.使苦恼；使痛苦', '1. I pray that you will have pity on my distress. 我请求你可怜可怜我的不幸遭遇。 2. I gripe more from habit than from genuine distress. 我抱怨是出于我的习惯，并非遭遇真正的不幸。 3. They sent a distress rocket. 他们发出了一枚呼救信号火箭。 4. His wild behavior was a great distress to his mother. 他的放荡的行为使他的母亲极为苦恼。 5. Don\'t distress yourself about it. 别为那件事苦恼了。', '副词: distressingly 过去式: distressed 过去分词: distressed 现在分词: distressing 第三人称单数: distresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gracious', '[\'ɡreɪʃəs]', 'adj.亲切的；高尚的；仁慈的；和蔼的；优雅的', '1. The Queen greeted the crowed with a gracious smile. 女王带着亲切的微笑向人群致意。 2. I received a gracious letter of acknowledgement. 我收到一封有礼貌的感谢信。 3. I\'ll be greatly honoured by your gracious presence. 如蒙光临，不胜荣幸。 4. Insist the gracious living style to experience the essential life spirit. 坚持以高尚的生活方式，体验生活本质的精神态度。', '副词: graciously 名词: graciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foresee', '[fɔːr\'siː]', 'v.预见；预知', '1. Can you foresee what will happen in the future? 你能预见将来会发生什么吗? 2. Nobody could foresee his running away. 没人预见到他的逃跑。 3. Few analysts foresaw that oil prices would rise so steeply. 几乎没有分析师能预见的到石油价格会上升得这么快。 4. Those who can foresee difficulties on their way to success may keep calm when they really appear. 在走向成功的路途中能够预见到困难的人在困难真正出现的时候常常能保持冷静的态度。', '形容词: foreseeable 名词: foreseer 过去式: foresaw 过去分词: foreseen 现在分词: foreseeing 第三人称单数: foresees');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bronze', '[brɑːnz]', 'n.青铜；青铜色；青铜制品；铜牌 adj.青铜制的；青铜色的 vt.使成青铜色', '1. The statue is made of bronze. 这座雕像是青铜铸成。 2. We fuse copper and tin to make bronze. 我们把铜和锡熔制成青铜。 3. The woods today are burnished bronze. 今天的树林是一片发亮的青铜色。 4. The sanctuary lamp and the metal furniture were bronze. 圣灯和一切金属器物都是青铜制品。 5. The sculpture was a bronze cast. 这个雕塑是青铜铸成的 6. His face had been bronzed by the sun. 他的脸被太阳晒成古铜色。', '形容词: bronzy 名词: bronzer 过去式: bronzed 过去分词: bronzed 现在分词: bronzing 第三人称单数: bronzes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('region', '[\'riːdʒən]', 'n.地区；范围；领域；地带；地域', '1. Most of the countries in the region have unstable economies. 这个地区大多数国家的经济都不稳定。 2. I guess there are much less people in the Arctic regions than here. 我想北极地区的人要比这里的少得多。 3. The region near the erupting volcano was evacuated rapidly. 火山爆发处附近已迅速撤空。 4. These small spiced cakes are a peculiarity of the region. 这些别有风味的小蛋糕是该地的特产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('limb', '[lɪm]', 'n.肢体；枝干；树枝 vt.肢解', '1. Men and women have four limbs; two arms and two legs. 人都有四肢，两只胳膊两条腿。 2. He stood up and stretched his limbs. 他站起来,伸了伸胳膊和腿。 3. A grey squirrel is scampering from limb to limb. 一只灰色的松鼠在树枝间跳来跳去。 4. The workers saw off a limb from the tree. 工人从树上锯下了一根大树枝。', '过去式: limbed 过去分词: limbed 现在分词: limbing 第三人称单数: limbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('marvelous', '[\'mɑːvələs]', 'adj.令人惊异的；非凡的 =<英>marvellous', '1. He had had the most marvelous experience. 他有过极奇特的经历。 2. These dogs have a marvelous sense of smell. 这些狗有非常敏锐的嗅觉。 3. You have a marvelous gift for science. 你有科学方面的非凡天赋。 4. Their performance was marvelous. 他们的演出太精彩了。', '副词: marvelously 名词: marvelousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('salmon', '[\'sæmən]', 'n.鲑；大马哈鱼；橙红色的', '1. He planed to go fishing for salmon on Sunday. 他计划星期天去钓鲑鱼。 2. Do you have any fresh salmon in at the moment? 现在有新鲜大马哈鱼卖吗？', '名词复数: salmon');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('treatment', '[\'triːtmənt]', 'n.治疗；对待；处理', '1. I tried every treatment the doctor suggested. 我试遍了医生建议的每一种疗法。 2. The treatment arrested the growth of the disease. 治疗抑制了病情的发展。 3. Unfortunately, they face unfair treatment and discrimination in that country. 不幸的是,他们在那个国家遭到了不公平对待和歧视。 4. This is a new product for the treatment of industrial waste. 这是一种处理工业废物的新产品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impudent', '[\'ɪmpjədənt]', 'adj.无礼的；鲁莽的；卑鄙的', '1. He was impudent enough to call me a fool. 他无礼至极，竟然叫我傻瓜。 2. That impudent boy put his tongue out at me. 那个无礼的男孩冲著我吐舌头。 3. The teacher threatened to kick the impudent pupil out of the room. 老师威胁着要把这无礼的小学生撵出教室。 4. We mustn\'t give way to these impudent demands. 我们对这些蛮横的要求不能让步。', '副词: impudently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seal', '[siːl]', 'n.封条；印章 n.海豹 v.密封；盖印；明确', '1. The seal on this bottle is broken. 这个瓶上的密封纸破开了。 2. This document carries the royal seal. 这份文件上盖有王室印章。 3. The first time I saw a seal was in an aquarium. 我第一次看见海豹是在水族馆里。 4. The envelope was firmly sealed. 这个信封封得很严实。', '形容词: sealable 过去式: sealed 过去分词: sealed 现在分词: sealing 第三人称单数: seals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('digestive', '[daɪ\'dʒestɪv]', 'adj.消化的；助消化的 n.消化药', '1. Although he is thin, he has good digestive power. 尽管他很瘦，他的消化能力挺好。 2. She suffered from digestive trouble. 她患有消化系统疾病。 3. Over the periods their saliva,a mild,digestive juice like our own,was converted into a poison that defies analysis even today. 经过若干演化阶段，蛇的唾液，一种温和的助消化的象人们的唾液一样的液体变成了甚至在今天也难以分析的毒液。', '副词: digestively 名词: digestiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attrition', '[ə\'trɪʃn]', 'n.摩擦；消耗；人员耗损', '1. Lube can ease attrition, and extend the using time of machines. 润滑剂能减少摩擦，延长机器寿命。 2. We should learn to respect others so as to avoid attrition and confliction. 我们应该学会尊重对方，避免摩擦和冲突。 3. But the objective of strategic attrition may also be achieved by campaigns of attrition. 但达到战略消耗目的的，还有战役的消耗战。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('literally', '[\'lɪtərəli]', 'adv.逐字地；按照字面上地；不夸张地；正确地；简直', '1. He translated this article literally. 他一字一句地翻译这篇文章。 2. Don\'t read the report literally now, just skim through it. 现在，不要逐字读报告，大致地看一下就可以了。 3. Idioms usually cannot be translated literally in another language. 成语通常不能照字面译成另一种语言。 4. He literally flew into the room. 他简直是飞也似地跑进了房间。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plague', '[pleɪɡ]', 'n.瘟疫；麻烦；灾祸 vt.折磨；烦扰；造成麻烦', '1. Plague came in the wake of earthquake. 地震之后紧跟着就是瘟疫。 2. A great plague was then raging in the city. 那时一场大瘟疫正在该城肆虐。 3. He\'s been avoiding me like the plague since our quarrel. 我们吵架以後，他一直如避蛇蝎似的躲著我。 4. A plague of locusts affected the harvest a lot this year. 蝗灾大大影响了今年的丰收。 5. A demon or spirit once was thought to plague sleeping people. 梦魔被认为折磨睡觉的人的魔鬼或灵魂', '名词: plaguer 过去式: plagued 过去分词: plagued 现在分词: plaguing 第三人称单数: plagues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('associate', '[ə\'soʊʃieɪt]', 'vt.联想；联合 n.伙伴；同事；同伴 adj.副的；共事的；有联系的 n.准学士学位获得者 vi.交往', '1. I always associate her with roses. 我总是把她与玫瑰花联想在一起。 2. We should associate ourselves with this large firm. 我们应该和这家大公司联合。 3. Mr. Miller is a business associate of our company. 米勒先生是我们公司的生意伙伴。 4. I got a new job and a new group of work associates. 我有了新工作和一班新同事。 5. He is an associate editor of the newspaper. 他是报纸的副主编。 6. You are wooing troubles if you associate with him. 你和他交往会招来麻烦。', '过去式: associated 过去分词: associated 现在分词: associating 第三人称单数: associates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impartial', '[ɪm\'pɑːrʃl]', 'adj.公正的；不偏不倚的', '1. He was not an impartial witness because of his affinity with the accused. 他不是公正的见证人，因为他与被告有姻亲关系。 2. He is an impartial judge. 他是一位公正的法官。 3. People in the city held the impartial judge in high regard. 这个城市的人们都很尊敬这位公正的法官。 4. An impartial judge can settle our argument. 公正的仲裁人能解决我们的争端。', '副词: impartially 名词: impartiality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('so-called', '[soʊ kɔːld]', 'adj.<贬>号称的；所谓的', '1. There is no so-called \"recipe for success\". 所谓“成功的诀窍”是不存在的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refrigerate', '[rɪ\'frɪdʒəreɪt]', 'v.使冷冻；使冷藏', '1. You had better refrigerate the beer before drinking it. 喝啤酒前你最好先把它冷冻一下。 2. The freezing machine can\'t refrigerate any more. It needs to be repaired. 这台冷冻机已经不制冷了，需要拿去修理。 3. Please refrigerate for a few hours before serving. 请将成品放到冰箱冷藏几个小时再食用。 4. You may also refrigerate our pet food for up to 6 months in a glass container. 你也可以把宠物粮放在玻璃器皿内并放到冰箱里，这样可以至多保存六个月。', '形容词: refrigerative 名词: refrigeration 过去式: refrigerated 过去分词: refrigerated 现在分词: refrigerating 第三人称单数: refrigerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wand', '[wɑːnd]', 'n.棒；棍；杖；魔杖；嫩枝；<美>箭靶', '1. The wand looks like a thick heavy pen. 这根棒看上去象一支粗大的钢笔。 2. Wipe the wand off before the first coat to prevent clumping. 把睫毛棒刷干净，避免结块。 3. The priestess drew a slender black wand from her belt. 女祭司从腰间拿出一只黑色细杖。 4. From that time, the entwined serpents became part of the wand itself. 从那以后，两条相互航线的蛇成为节杖的组成部分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('touching', '[\'tʌtʃɪŋ]', 'adj.动人的；感人的 prep.关于；有关 动词touch的现在分词.', '1. This is the most touching story I have ever heard. 这是我听到过的最动人的故事。 2. His farewell speech was very touching. 他的告别演讲非常感人。 3. She asked many question touching my family and school. 她问了我许多关于家庭和学校的问题。 4. He wrote a article touching a environment pollution. 他写了一篇有关环境污染的文章。 5. The two wires were touching. 那两条金属线搭在一起了。（《牛津高阶英汉双解词典》）', '副词: touchingly 名词: touchingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delay', '[dɪ\'leɪ]', 'v.耽搁；推迟；延误 n.耽搁；延期；推迟', '1. It was impossible to delay her at such a crisis. 在这样一个紧要关头来耽搁她是不可能的。 2. We decided to delay our wedding until next year. 我们决定把婚礼推迟到明年。 3. Our plane was delayed by fog. 我们的飞机因大雾而误点了。 4. The weather is responsible for the delay. 由于天气关系才耽搁了。', '名词: delayer 过去式: delayed 过去分词: delayed 现在分词: delaying 第三人称单数: delays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('herb', '[ɜːrb]', 'n.药草；香草', '1. He alighted on a rare medical herb. 他偶然找到了一种稀有的草药。 2. I had to take the herb tea although it\'s bitter. 虽然汤药很苦，我还是不得不喝了。 3. The essence drawn out from this medicinal herb is good for high blood pressure. 从这种药草提炼出来的精华对治疗高血压有效。 4. This herb can act as an antidote against snakebite. 这种药草可以用作被蛇咬后的解毒药。', '形容词: herby');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('probity', '[\'proʊbəti]', 'n.诚实；廉洁；正直', '1. Jobbery crime is an extreme form of social corruption which has destoried the political probity and social justice. 职务犯罪是社会腐败的一种极端形式，它腐蚀政治清明，破坏经济发展，损害社会正义。 2. But there is scant risk of too much fiscal probity in Washington. 但在华盛顿再多财政廉洁也没有大风险。 3. The administrator gained much public praise because of his efficiency and probity. 这位行政官因其高效和廉洁而受到了人民的称赞。 4. Probity will command respect everywhere. 为人正直无论在哪里都会受人尊敬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('awkward', '[\'ɔːkwərd]', 'adj.尴尬的；笨拙的；（设计）别扭的', '1. It\'s a little awkward, because he\'s my friend but I\'m still his boss. 他是我朋友,而我又是他老板,这真有点尴尬。 2. He felt awkward and uncomfortable. 他感到尴尬和不舒服。 3. He seemed as awkward and rough as ever. 他跟从前一样拙笨和粗鲁。 4. Swans are surprisingly awkward on the land. 天鹅在陆地上笨的出奇。', '副词: awkwardly 名词: awkwardness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unsubstantiated', '[ˌʌnsəb\'stænʃieɪtɪd]', 'adj.无事实根据的', '1. His attack of the president was unsubstantiated. 说他袭击总统是没有事实根据的。 2. Many newspapers quoted figures that are unsubstantiated. 许多报纸采用了未经证实的数字。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('utilitarian', '[ˌjuːtɪlɪ\'teriən]', 'adj.功利的；实用的 n.功利主义者', '1. In the selection, he attempts to clarify the utilitarian standard. 在这段选文中，他试图对功利标准作一清楚表述。 2. The buildings were utilitarian rather than decorative. 这些建筑是实用性的，而不是装饰性的。 3. He is very down to earth and is a real utilitarian. 他那个人很现实, 是个十足的功利主义者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unpredictable', '[ˌʌnprɪ\'dɪktəbl]', 'adj.不可预知的', '1. A young woman spends a curiously unpredictable day with a stranger. 一个年青女子和一个陌生人，度过了奇怪和不可预知的一天。 2. What tied it all together was a foundation in the blues, a reliance on group interplay and unpredictable improvisation. 而将这些形式连接在一起的是蓝调音乐的这一根基，以及依靠的是整个乐队成员的交互演奏和不可预知的即兴演奏。', '副词: unpredictably 名词: unpredictability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rehabilitate', '[ˌriːə\'bɪlɪteɪt]', 'vt.使恢复；修复；改造', '1. He was set free and rehabilitated as chief engineer. 他被释放并恢复总工程师职务。 2. Our disgraced teacher was publicly rehabilitated by school authorities. 学校当局为我们的蒙受耻辱的老师公开恢复了名誉。 3. There was no money to rehabilitate the tower. 没有资金修复那座塔。 4. Does prison help rehabilitate criminals? 监狱能帮助改造罪犯吗?', '形容词: rehabilitatable 名词: rehabilitation 过去式: rehabilitated 过去分词: rehabilitated 现在分词: rehabilitating 第三人称单数: rehabilitates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transact', '[træn\'zækt]', 'v.办理；交易；谈判；进行', '1. When will I transact the procedure of going board? 我该什么时间办理登机手续呢？ 2. I want to transact the call display service. 我想办理来电显示业务。 3. I understand that unless I remain registered with CIB, I cannot transact insurance broking business on behalf of the Appointing Member. 本人明白除非本人在联会的注册持续有效，否则不得代表委任本人的会员进行保险经纪业务。', '名词: transactor 过去式: transacted 过去分词: transacted 现在分词: transacting 第三人称单数: transacts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mighty', '[\'maɪti]', 'adj.强大的；巨大的 adv.很；极其', '1. The United Kingdom was a mighty empire before World War I. 英联邦在第一次世界大战前曾是一个强大的帝国。 2. The mighty empire finally crumbled. 这个强大的帝国最终瓦解了。 3. The mighty iceberg came into view. 巨大的冰山出现在眼前。 4. A mighty force was about to break loose. 一股巨大的力量即将迸发而出。 5. He was mighty hungry. 他肚子很饿。', '比较级: mightier 最高级: mightiest 名词: mightiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fracture', '[\'fræktʃər]', 'n.破碎；骨折 vt.破碎；破裂 vi.断裂', '1. A fellow team member says it was a clean fracture without complications. 一位队友表示这只是纯粹的锁骨破碎，没有任何并发症。 2. He had several injuries, including three fractures. 他多处受伤，其中三处骨折。 3. If you sneeze too hard, you can fracture a rib. 打喷嚏太用力的话肋骨可能会骨折。 4. Many people predicted that the party would fracture and split. 很多人预言该党将分崩离析。 5. Her leg fractured in two places. 她的腿有两处骨折。', '过去式: fractured 过去分词: fractured 现在分词: fracturing 第三人称单数: fractures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consequently', '[\'kɑːnsəkwentli]', 'adv.因此；所以', '1. The scandal being exposed, he was removed from office consequently. 他的丑闻被曝光了，他因此被调离了职位。 2. The company went bankrupt and consequently he lost his job. 公司破产,因此他失业了。 3. My car broke down and consequently I was late. 我的汽车坏了 4. The rain was heavy, and consequently the road was flooded. 雨很大, 所以路被淹没了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grudge', '[ɡrʌdʒ]', 'n.怨恨；恶意 vt.不愿；吝惜；嫉妒', '1. He harbors a secret grudge against his father. 他对父亲暗怀不满。 2. I was willing to settle my grudge with Harrison. 我原意解决我和哈里森的怨恨。 3. I always feel he has a grudge against me, although I don\'t know why. 我总觉得他讨厌我，但我不知道为什么。 4. He has a grudge against me. 他对我有恶意. 5. I grudge paying so much for such inferior goods. 我不愿花这么多钱买次品。', '副词: grudgingly 名词: grudger 过去式: grudged 过去分词: grudged 现在分词: grudging 第三人称单数: grudges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sensory', '[\'sensəri]', 'adj.知觉的；感觉的；知觉器官的', '1. Although postural control relies on sensory feedback, motion sickness is really a sign that the motor-control system is going haywire. 尽管姿势的维持仰赖知觉的回馈，晕车感其实是运动控制系统混乱的前兆。 2. For the genesis of its ideas mathematics gradually turned from the sensory to the intellectual faculties. 由于数学概念的起源，使它逐渐从感觉的学科转向思维的学科。 3. Changes in sensory perception are the most sensitive indicators of the presence of nitrogen dioxide. 感觉的改变是二氧化氮存在的最灵敏的标志。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drawback', '[\'drɔːbæk]', 'n.缺点；退税；退款；不利条件；弊', '1. The great drawback to living near a main road is noise. 住在大街旁最大的缺点是噪音。 2. Everything has its drawbacks. 凡事都有不足之处。 3. Many people are talking about the impact of export drawback system reform on the economy in China these days. 这些天来许多人都在讨论出口退税制度改革对我国经济的影响。 4. Illness is a great drawback to a learner. 患病对学生来说是大为不利的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('congenial', '[kən\'dʒiːniəl]', 'adj.同性质的；适意的；趣味相同的；友善的', '1. No fuss was made in my day if a new writer took from an old one whatever material he found congenial. 在我那个时代，如果一个新作家从一个老作家的作品中摘取了他能用的合适材料，并不受到反对。 2. In the next year he obtained, through the good offices of an old friend, a post with a publishing firm which, though not highly paid, he found more congenial. 第二年，通过一个老朋友帮忙，他在一家出版公司谋到一个职位，薪水虽不高，却更令他感到惬意。 3. They are of congenial temper. 他们的性情相投。 4. I found him very congenial. 我发现他跟人很合得来。', '副词: congenially 名词: congeniality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('smoothly', '[\'smuːðli]', 'adv.平滑地；流畅地', '1. One end of the wing tapers smoothly. 机翼的一端平滑地变成尖细状。 2. Chinese leaders told ASEM that their priority was to keep their own economy running smoothly. 中国的领导人们，告诉亚欧会议，他们的优先权将会保持他们自己的经济平滑地运行。 3. He hadn\'t learned to bow smoothly yet. 他还没学会流畅地拉琴。 4. A ball can roll smoothly on a plane. 球可以在水平面上流畅地滚动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adhere', '[əd\'hɪr]', 'vi.遵守；坚持；粘附', '1. They failed to adhere to our original agreement. 他们未能遵守我们原定的协议。 2. We should adhere to our opinions. 我们应当坚持我们的意见。 3. We adhere to the principle stand of marxism. 我们坚持马克思主义思想原则。 4. The new paint won\'t adhere to the walls so I\'ll have to strip it all off and start from scratch. 新涂的油漆粘不住墙壁,因此我得把它全部刮掉,重新刷过。', '过去式: adhered 过去分词: adhered 现在分词: adhering 第三人称单数: adheres');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bruise', '[bruːz]', 'n.瘀青；擦伤；挫伤 vi.碰伤；擦伤 vt.使挫伤', '1. His face is a mass of bruise after the fight. 他打完架后脸上青一块紫一块的。 2. She is lucky to get off with just a few bruise. 她幸免于难,只是有几处擦伤。 3. She had a dilly of a bruise on her arm. 她手臂上有一块显眼的伤痕。 4. It can range from a minor Bruise or sprain to a skull fracture with Brain damage or a spinal-cord injury with paralysis. 其范围从小型挫伤或扭伤到大脑受损的头颅裂开或麻痹性脊椎伤害。 5. Soft fruit bruises easily. 细嫩的水果容易碰损。 6. She fell and bruised her knee. 她摔倒在地，膝盖上起了紫血块。', '过去式: bruised 过去分词: bruised 现在分词: bruising 第三人称单数: bruises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rescue', '[\'reskjuː]', 'vt.营救；援救 n.营救；救援', '1. He dived from the bridge to rescue the drowning child. 他从桥上跳入水中去抢救那溺水儿童。 2. Had Jim not dived in to rescue him, the boy would have drowned. 如果不是吉姆跳下水去救，那小孩早就淹死了。 3. The government has rescued the firm from bankruptcy by giving them a grant. 政府拨款给这家公司使其免于破产。 4. The rescue attempt was impeded by bad weather. 营救工作受到恶劣天气的妨碍。', '形容词: rescuable 名词: rescuer 过去式: rescued 过去分词: rescued 现在分词: rescuing 第三人称单数: rescues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('combination', '[ˌkɑːmbɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.结合；结合到一起的事物或人；密码', '1. It is the combination of wit and political analysis that makes his articles so readable. 他的生花妙笔与政治分析相得益彰，使他的文章脍炙人口。 2. The firm is working on a new product in combination with several overseas partners. 公司正在联合几家海外合伙人制造新产品。 3. A combination of factors led to her decision to resign. 综合各种因素之後她决定辞职。 4. If you want to open the lock, you must know the combination. 如果你想要打开这把锁,你必须知道密码。', '形容词: combinational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('threshold', '[\'θreʃhoʊld]', 'n.门槛；开端；界限；入口', '1. The cabin has a flat stone for a threshold. 这间小屋用一条扁平的石头做门槛。 2. The treaty will be the threshold of lasting peace. 这个条约将成为持久和平的开端。 3. He was on the threshold of his career. 他的事业刚刚起步。 4. The tax threshold for a pensioner is $6,000. 领退休金的人的纳税起点是六千美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dilemma', '[dɪ\'lemə]', 'n.困境；进退两难', '1. In the process of modern urban development, we often find ourselves in a dilemma. 在都市的发展中,我们往往会陷入困境。 2. The bad weather put us in a dilemma——shall we move on or go back? 糟糕的天气使我们进退两难——是继续前进呢,还是打道回府？', '形容词: dilemmatic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lethargy', '[\'leθərdʒi]', 'n.昏睡；倦怠；无精打采', '1. Several hours after the surgery, she was still in her lethargy. 手术过後几小时,她仍然昏睡不醒。 2. She was suddenly overcome by lethargy. 她突然委靡不振。 3. Winston roused himself a little from his lethargy. 温斯顿从懒洋洋的惰性中振作起一些来。 4. The bird\'s lethargy in the morning was unusual. 这只鸟在早上就无生气,很不寻常。', '名词复数: lethargies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('terminal', '[\'tɜːrmɪnl]', 'n.末端；终点站；终点；终端机；航站楼 adj.末端的；终点的；晚期的；（每）学期的', '1. That terminal is live. 那个接头有电。 2. A record message is played when the airport bus approaches the terminal. 当机场班车接近终点时，播放了注意事项录音。 3. I\'ll keep with you to the bus terminal. 我陪你到公共汽车终点站。 4. Please wait for me at the bus terminal. 请在公共汽车终点站等我。 5. Telomere locates on the terminal of DNA containing repeat DNA sequence. 端粒是位于染色体末端的串联重复核苷酸序列。', '副词: terminally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fowl', '[faʊl]', 'n.禽；禽肉 v.猎捕野禽', '1. It is a fowl which needs to be carved. 这是需要切分的鸡禽。 2. Fowl is not part of a traditional brunch. 禽肉不是传统的早午餐的一部分。 3. Roast fowl was served at the dinner. 正餐吃的是烤禽肉。', '名词: fowler 名词复数: fowl 过去式: fowled 过去分词: fowled 现在分词: fowling 第三人称单数: fowls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('casualty', '[\'kæʒuəlti]', 'n.事故；伤亡者；伤亡人数；<英>急诊室', '1. The cottage was a casualty of the forest fire. 那小屋被森林大火烧毁。 2. She read through the casualty list anxiously. 她忧虑地把伤亡人员名单从头到尾看了一遍。 3. The casualty of the traffic accident was a doleful record. 这一交通事故地伤亡人数是一个令人伤心的记录.', '名词复数: casualties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perplex', '[pər\'pleks]', 'v.使困惑；使糊涂；使复杂化', '1. When new math was introduced into schools, many parents were perplexed by it. 当学校开设新的数学课时，许多家长对此感到迷惑不解。 2. Faced with that dilemma, he was perplexed. 他面对进退两难的局面，不知如何是好。', '副词: perplexingly 过去式: perplexed 过去分词: perplexed 现在分词: perplexing 第三人称单数: perplexes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('endure', '[ɪn\'dʊr]', 'vt.容忍 vi.忍耐；持久；持续', '1. I could not endure the insolence of his behaviour. 我不能再忍受他那傲慢无礼的行为了。 2. I cannot endure listening to that any longer. 我再也不耐烦听那一套了。 3. If help doesn\'t come,we must endure to the end. 如果没人来帮助,我们必须忍耐到底。 4. They vowed their love would endure forever. 他们海誓山盟地久天长。', '过去式: endured 过去分词: endured 现在分词: enduring 第三人称单数: endures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('composed', '[kəm\'poʊzd]', 'adj.镇静的；沉着的；由…组成的', '1. He was pale but perfectly composed. 他脸色苍白，却十分镇静。 2. Though badly frightened, she remained outwardly composed. 她虽然非常害怕，但表面上依然很镇静。 3. The performer was composed as she readied herself for her entrance on stage. 这位演员在准备上场时沉着冷静。 4. Water is composed of hydrogen and oxygen. 水由氢和氧组成。', '副词: composedly 名词: composedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('horn', '[hɔːrn]', 'n.喇叭；触角；角质；号 v.强行介入', '1. The driver tooted his horn as he approached the bend. 开车的人在快要转弯时按响了喇叭。 2. The driver hooted his horn (at us). 司机(冲著我们)鸣喇叭。 3. The rhinoceros has one horn on its nose. 犀牛鼻子上有一个角。 4. The lark\'s on the wing, the snail\'s on the horn. 云雀在空中飞翔，蜗牛伸出触角爬行。 5. Although he was not invited,Henry managed to horn in on Myra\'s wedding. 尽管亨利没有被邀请，他还是设法闯来参加迈拉的婚礼。', '名词: hornist 过去式: horned 过去分词: horned 现在分词: horning 第三人称单数: horns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exalted', '[ɪɡ\'zɔːltɪd]', 'adj.高位的；高尚的；欣喜的 动词exalt的过去式和过去分词.', '1. I met a person of exalted position. 我遇上一个地位很高的人。 2. She was the only woman to rise to such an exalted position. 她是唯一高升到如此显赫地位的女人。 3. Not all those who emigrated to America did so for exalted reasons. 移民来美并不是个个都为了崇高的目标。 4. They were exalted by the news of the victory. 他们因听到胜利的消息而兴高采烈。', '副词: exaltedly 名词: exaltedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ragged', '[\'ræɡɪd]', 'adj.衣衫褴褛的；粗糙的；刺耳的；（外形）不规则的；不完美的', '1. The poor boy was ashamed of his ragged cloths. 这个穷孩子为自己的破衣服感到难为情。 2. The ragged man drags a waggon of rag fragments. 那个衣衫褴褛的人拉着一货车破布碎片。 3. Ragged cuts heal slowly and often poorly. 粗糙的伤口愈合慢，而且不好。 4. The spiders lie on their sides, translucent and ragged, their legs drying in knots. 蜘蛛们侧躺着，身体半透明而且粗糙，腿干枯关节突起。', '副词: raggedly 名词: raggedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embroider', '[ɪm\'brɔɪdər]', 'v.刺绣；镶边；装饰', '1. She embroidered the cushion with flowers. 她把垫子绣上了花。 2. She embroiders very well. 她很会刺绣。 3. He is likely to embroider the truth a bit. 他往往会修饰一下事实。 4. He used a little poetic licence to embroider a good story. 他用了一些创新的词语，使动人的故事锦上添花。', '名词: embroiderer 过去式: embroidered 过去分词: embroidered 现在分词: embroidering 第三人称单数: embroiders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('terrestrial', '[tə\'restriəl]', 'adj.陆地的；陆生的；地球的 n.地球生物', '1. Men live on the terrestrial parts of the earth. 人们住在地球上的陆地部分。 2. Aquatic food chains are different from terrestrial ones. 水生食物链不同于陆地食物链。 3. Although they can swim, the polar bears are terrestrial animals. 北极熊虽然会游泳，但也是陆栖动物。 4. A terrestrial globe is one that represents the earth. 地球仪是表现地球的器具。', '副词: terrestrially 名词: terrestrialness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('investigate', '[ɪn\'vestɪɡeɪt]', 'v.调查；研究', '1. The police are investigating the murder. 警察正在调查这件谋杀案。 2. We might be able to help you; I\'ll investigate the possibilities. 我们也许能帮助你，我要研究一下这种可能性。', '形容词: investigable 过去式: investigated 过去分词: investigated 现在分词: investigating 第三人称单数: investigates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transparent', '[træns\'pærənt]', 'adj.透明的；明显的；清晰的', '1. Plain glass is transparent. 普通的白玻璃是透明的。 2. The insect\'s wings are almost transparent. 这昆虫的翅膀几乎是透明的。 3. It was transparent that her pride was hurt. 很显然，她的自尊心受到了伤害。 4. Your words are a transparent lie. 你所说的明显是谎言。', '副词: transparently 名词: transparentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dungeon', '[\'dʌndʒən]', 'n.地牢；土牢；城堡主塔', '1. They were driven into a dark dungeon. 他们被人驱赶进入一个黑暗的地牢。 2. The poor peasant was thrown into a dungeon. 那个可怜的农民被投进了地牢。 3. In the first act the curtain goes up on a dungeon in a landlord\'s house. 第一幕启幕时，舞台上现出了地主家里的一个地牢。 4. This place is awful like a dungeon! 这地方真要命，象个土牢！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relic', '[\'relɪk]', 'n.神圣的遗物；遗迹；纪念物', '1. This stone axe is a relic of ancient times. 这把石斧是古代的遗物。 2. Gold is still a barbaric relic whose value rises only when inflation is high. 黄金仍然只是未开化时代的遗物，其价值只在通涨高企时才会上升。 3. The calorie is a historical relic. 卡是历史的遗迹。 4. The building stands as the last remaining relic of the town\'s cotton industry. 这座建筑物是小镇棉纺业仅存的遗迹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ingredient', '[ɪn\'ɡriːdiənt]', 'n.成分；原料；配料；因素', '1. Coconut is a basic ingredient for many curries. 椰子是多种咖喱菜的基本成分。 2. Mix all the ingredients in a bowl. 将原料放在盆里调匀. 3. There is a list of ingredients on the side of the packet. 包装袋的边上印有所含配料表。 4. Humor is an effective ingredient of a speech. 幽默是演讲中效果极佳的一个因素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insurance', '[ɪn\'ʃʊrəns]', 'n.保险；保险费；安全保障', '1. I am an insurance broker. 我是一名保险经纪人。 2. He works in an insurance company. 他在一家保险公司上班。 3. I have paid my car insurance. 我已经交了汽车保险费。 4. His insurance is $ 300 a year. 他的保险费是每年三百美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('governor', '[\'ɡʌvərnər]', 'n.统治者；管理者；理事；州长；总督；调节器', '1. The mob revolted against the governor. 暴民起来反抗统治者。 2. He established himself as governor of the province. 他当上了省长。 3. The governor decreed a day of mourning. 地方长官发布哀悼一日的命令。 4. It looks like the governor\'s personal guard. 看起来就像管理者的私人保卫者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reservoir', '[\'rezərvwɑːr]', 'n.水库；储藏；蓄水池；积蓄', '1. Fresh water was at a premium after the reservoir was contaminated. 在水库被污染之后,清水便因稀而贵了。 2. They open the sluice gates of reservoir. 他们打开水库的闸门。 3. His mind is a reservoir of facts. 他的心是事实的储藏处。 4. To begin to understand why, remember that water in a reservoir naturally flows preferentially to any crack in the dam. 要探究原因，可以联想一下蓄水池的水，当水坝有裂缝时，水很自然的会先由裂缝流出。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stationery', '[\'steɪʃəneri]', 'n.文具；信笺', '1. He\'s been helping himself to my stationery. 他未经许可一直用我的文具。 2. My stationery cupboard is full of paper. 我的文具柜塞满了纸。 3. The letter is typed on his office stationery. 这件信打在他办公室专用信纸上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outline', '[\'aʊtlaɪn]', 'n.大纲；轮廓 vt.概述；画出轮廓', '1. He wrote down the outline of his lecture. 他写下演讲的提纲。 2. She drew the outline with a sure hand. 她笔力雄健地画出了轮廓。 3. He saw the outline of the house in the moonlight. 在月光下,他看到了那座屋子的轮廓。 4. At the interview, she outlined what i would be doing. 在谈话时,她概述了我将要干的工作。', '过去式: outlined 过去分词: outlined 现在分词: outlining 第三人称单数: outlines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trigger', '[\'trɪɡər]', 'v.使发生；触发；使运行 n.扳机；起因', '1. Price increases will trigger off demands for wage increases. 价格上涨会激发人们增长工资的要求。 2. The odour of food may trigger people\'s appetite. 食物的香味能引起人的食欲。 3. A detonator is used to trigger an explosive device. 雷管用来引爆爆炸装置。 4. I pulled the trigger and the gun went off. 我一扣扳机，枪就响了。', '过去式: triggered 过去分词: triggered 现在分词: triggering 第三人称单数: triggers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fusion', '[\'fjuːʒn]', 'n.融合；结合；熔合；核聚变', '1. There is now a worrying fusion of information and entertainment. 现在信息和娱乐已经出现令人忧虑的相互融合。 2. She was a fusion of the dreamer and doer. 她是空想者和实干者的结合。 3. The movie displayed a perfect fusion of image and sound. 这部电影展示了音响与影像的完美结合。 4. Brass is formed by the fusion of copper and zinc. 黄铜是由铜和锌熔合制成的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transform', '[træns\'fɔːm]', 'vt.改变；转换 vi.改变；变形；变态', '1. She is responsible for the character part of the hero\'s devoted mother. 她负责这个主人公的忠诚的母亲的角色部分。 2. The magician transformed the frog into a princess. 魔术师把青蛙变成了公主。 3. His plans were transformed overnight into reality. 他的计划迅速变为现实。 4. We should try to transform heat into power. 我们应该设法将热转化为能量。', '形容词: transformable 过去式: transformed 过去分词: transformed 现在分词: transforming 第三人称单数: transforms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alienate', '[\'eɪliəneɪt]', 'vt.使疏远；离间；让与；麻木', '1. We\'d better not alienate ourselves from the colleagues. 我们最好还是不要与同事们疏远。 2. The Prime Minister\'s policy alienated many of her followers. 首相的政策使很多拥护她的人疏远了她。 3. His attempts to alienate the two friends failed. 他离间那一对朋友的企图失败了。 4. She tried to alienate him from his brother 她企图离间他和他的兄弟。', '名词: alienator 过去式: alienated 过去分词: alienated 现在分词: alienating 第三人称单数: alienates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('composition', '[ˌkɑːmpə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.成分；作品；组织；作文；合成物', '1. We examined the rock to find out its composition. 我们检验了这一石块,想弄清它的构成成分。 2. He played many of his compositions for me. 他为我演奏了他的许多乐曲。 3. `Swan Lake\' is one of Tchaikovsky\'s best-known compositions. 《天鹅湖》是柴可夫斯基最著名的作品之一。 4. I have no idea who decided the composition of the committee. 我不知道委员会的成员是由谁选定的。', '形容词: compositional 副词: compositionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ideology', '[ˌaɪdi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.意识形态；空论；观念学', '1. An obsolete ideology can hamper an economy. 过时的意识形态会束缚经济。 2. Nothing lay outside the scheme of our ideology. 我们的意识形态领域包罗万象。 3. Consensus came at the cost of ideology. 共识是通过放弃意识形态立场而获得的。 4. His attitude to ownership is rooted in communist ideology. 他的所有制观点源自共产主义思想。', '名词: ideologist 名词复数: ideologies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reproduction', '[ˌriːprə\'dʌkʃn]', 'n.再现；复制；生殖；幼树', '1. Her description of the meeting is an exact reproduction of the reunion. 她对会面的描述是这次团聚的真实再现。 2. Digital photography has more affinity to painting than to reproduction. 摄影提供了工具去再现尽可能接近的真实。 3. The quality of reproduction isn\'t very good on this recording. 这次录音复制的质量不怎么好。 4. Reproduction cost documents the cost to build an exact duplicate. 复制文件的成本费用，建立一个确切的重复。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('formation', '[fɔːr\'meɪʃn]', 'n.形成；队形；编队；构造；[地]地层', '1. Let us now examine the process of its formation. 我们现在就来研究这个形成过程。 2. School life has a great influence on the formation of a child\'s character. 学校生活对小孩个性的形成有很大影响。 3. The airplanes few over in formation. 飞机编成队形在空中飞过。 4. The troops lined up in parade formation. 部队排成阅兵队形。', '形容词: formational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distort', '[dɪ\'stɔːrt]', 'vt.歪曲；扭曲；变形 vi.歪曲', '1. The reporter distorted the facts. 记者们歪曲了事实。 2. How dare he distort the facts so brazenly! 他怎么敢如此肆无忌惮地歪曲事实！ 3. The government was accused of having systematically distorted the protester\'s case. 政府因为有计划地歪曲抗议者的观点而受到责难。 4. This journalist distorted the spokesman\'s remarks. 这名记者曲解了该发言人的话。 5. The bias of a reporter can easily distort the news. 记者的偏见很容易歪曲新闻的报导。', '名词: distorter 过去式: distorted 过去分词: distorted 现在分词: distorting 第三人称单数: distorts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impromptu', '[ɪm\'prɑːmptuː]', 'adj.即席的；即兴的，临时的 adv.即兴地，无准备地 n.即兴之作；即兴曲', '1. It usually take me more than three weeks to prepare a good impromptu speech. 为了准备一则即席的好讲辞，我通常要三个星期以上。 2. An impromptu visit broke up the long afternoon. 突然的造访打破了漫长的午后时光。 3. She played a tune impromptu. 她即席演奏了一曲。 4. His call for a book of the trains had been a sheer piece of impromptu. 他打听火车时刻表只是一段纯粹的即兴曲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lawsuit', '[\'lɔːsuːt]', 'n.诉讼；控诉', '1. They threatened him with a lawsuit. 他们以诉讼来威胁他。 2. He raised the question of the cost of the lawsuit. 他提出了诉讼费用的难题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rodent', '[\'roʊdnt]', 'n.啮齿动物 adj.啮齿目的', '1. I\'ll dig like a psychotic rodent if I have to. 我可以挖的像发疯的啮齿动物。 2. And Oregon, \"The Beaver State,\" borrows its nickname from the large, flat-tailed rodent that uses trees to build dams. 俄勒冈州，也成为河狸之州，从一种用树木建大坝的大尾巴啮齿动物得来的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affection', '[ə\'fekʃn]', 'n.影响；感情；喜爱；慈爱', '1. He\'s so susceptible that she easily gained his affection. 他易受感情影响，所以她很轻易就得到了他的爱。 2. You appear to me to allow nothing for the influence of friendship and affection. 我觉得你未免否定了友谊和感情对于一个人的影响。 3. Don\'t squander your affection on him, he\'ll never love you. 不要把感情浪费在他身上，他是永远不会爱你的。 4. He\'s so susceptible that she easily gained his affection. 他易受感情影响，所以她很轻易就得到了他的爱。', '形容词: affectional 副词: affectionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bill', '[bɪl]', 'n.帐单；钞票；清单；议案；海报；节目单；锚钩；鸟喙；帽舌 v.开帐单；把 ... 列成表；用海报宣传；(鸟嘴)接触；爱抚 Bill n.比尔(男子名)', '1. A 10% service charge is added on to the bill. 帐单上包括了百分之十的服务费。 2. I have a 5-dollar bill. 我有一张5美元的钞票。 3. A bill came along with the package. 清单与包裹一并到达。 4. After a long debate the bill was passed. 经长时间的辩论，议案获得通过。 5. We\'ll bill you next week for your purchases. 下周我们将把你购买的物品开账单给你。 6. Bill Gates is an American citizen. 比尔·盖茨是美国公民。', '形容词: billable 过去式: billed 过去分词: billed 现在分词: billing 第三人称单数: bills');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('modulate', '[\'mɑːdʒəleɪt]', 'v.调整；调节（声音）；变调', '1. The speaker had a really noble voice which he could modulate with great skill. 这位演说者有副相当好的嗓子，他能很技巧地调整它。 2. He knows when to move upstage,when to modulate his voice,and when to throw away a line. 他懂得什么时候该移向舞台后方，什么时候该调整声调，以及什么时候该轻轻带过一句台词。 3. Please modulate the sound on the TV. 请调节一下电视机的音量。 4. Moreover, it has been shown to induce steatosis, modulate apoptosis, and increase cellular oncogenic potential. 更且，它会引起脂肪变性，调节细胞凋亡，增加细胞的致癌性。', '形容词: modulative 名词: modulability 过去式: modulated 过去分词: modulated 现在分词: modulating 第三人称单数: modulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lethal', '[\'liːθl]', 'adj.致命的；危险的；有效的', '1. Pot-holes can be lethal for the unwary cyclist. 路上的坑坑洼洼骑车的人一不小心就有致命危险。 2. In situation like this, she wish she have a gun or some lethal weapon. 在这种情况下，她真希望自己有一把枪或什么致命武器。 3. It was a potentially lethal mixture of drugs. 这种混合药物有很大的潜在危险。 4. This time it was covered in snow and ice and in a lethal condition. 这一次该山崖布满了雪和冰,条件实在不佳。', '副词: lethally 名词: lethality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overwhelm', '[ˌoʊvər\'welm]', 'vt.打击；压倒；使感动；淹没；打败', '1. No difficulty can overwhelm us. 困难压不倒我们。 2. If I cannot overwhelm with my quality, I will overwhelm with my quantity. 如果我不能以质量压倒，我就一定要以数量压倒。 3. Your kindness quite overwhelmed me. 你的好意使我感激难言。 4. The village was overwhelmed when the floods came. 这个村庄在洪水泛滥时被淹没了。', '过去式: overwhelmed 过去分词: overwhelmed 现在分词: overwhelming 第三人称单数: overwhelms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('offspring', '[\'ɔːfsprɪŋ]', 'n.后代；子孙；产物', '1. His offspring are diligent and intelligent. 他的后代既勤奋又聪明。 2. The hybrid offspring of a zebra and a horse. 杂交斑马斑马与马杂交的后代 3. His offspring inherit the estate. 他的孩子继承了房地产。 4. How do parents pass genes on to their offspring? 父母是怎样把基因遗传给自己的子女的？', '名词复数: offspring');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lichen', '[\'laɪkən]', 'n.地衣；青苔', '1. Caribou eat moss, lichen and green plants. 北美驯鹿的主要食物是地衣、苔藓和绿色植物。 2. The stone stairway was covered with lichen. 那石级长满了地衣。 3. The rock is full of lichen. 岩石上长满了青苔。 4. Lichen is the dominant life-form that covers the surfaces of stones and trees. 青苔是生长在石头和树木表面的主要生物。', '形容词: lichenous 过去式: lichened 过去分词: lichened 现在分词: lichening 第三人称单数: lichens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('merchant', '[\'mɜːrtʃənt]', 'n.商人；店主；专家 adj.商业的；商船的 n.（班轮提单）货方；签约方', '1. The merchant had received a shipment of tea. 这个商人收到了一船茶叶。 2. The merchant decided to use camels to carry his goods across the desert. 商人决定用骆驼载运货物穿过沙漠。 3. The merchant\'s cash sales each day were $300. 那店主一天有300美元的现金售货收入。 4. Art experts, who have already dated the painting to this time, say the Heidelberg discovery is a breakthrough and the earliest mention linking the merchant\'s wife to the portrait. 美术专家们还称，关于此画，海德尔堡的发现是一个突破，并且是最早提出把商人的妻子和人物肖像结合起来这一说法的。 5. This is a merchant bank. 这是个商业银行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crustacean', '[krʌ\'steɪʃn]', 'n.甲壳类动物 adj.甲壳纲的', '1. Every crustacean has a layer of shell, which is also called the carapace. 甲壳动物体外都有一层几丁质外壳, 称为甲壳。 2. The fair shrimp, Chirocephalus nankinensis, is the large branchiopoda crustacean. 丰年虫是我国特有的大型淡水鳃足类甲壳动物,其休眠卵具饰纹结构。 3. Phospholipids also appear to be essential in crustacean physiology. 甲壳类虽可生合成磷脂质,但能力十分有限。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annex', '[ə\'neks]', 'vt.并吞；附加；获得 n.附件；附属物；附属建筑物', '1. Japan annexed Korea in 1910. 日本在1910年吞并了朝鲜。 2. In the years immediately preceding the outbreak of war in1939, Hitler succeeded in annexing various parts of Europe to Germany without firing a shot. 在1939年大战爆发的前几年，希特勒没开一抢而成功地把欧洲许多地区并吞为德国领土。 3. Happiness is not always annexed to wealth. 财富并不一定会带来幸福。 4. A new wing has been annexed to the hospital. 医院已经增建了一个新侧楼。 5. Any annex is the integral part of this contract. 本合同一切附件均为本合同的有效组成部分。', '形容词: annexational 名词: annexation 过去式: annexed 过去分词: annexed 现在分词: annexing 第三人称单数: annexes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('numerous', '[\'nuːmərəs]', 'adj.为数众多的；许多', '1. The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe. 地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。 2. Those birds have become more numerous lately. 近来那种鸟变得越来越多了。 3. Numerous interruptions have prevented me from finishing my work. 我屡遭搅扰以致工作未能完成。 4. He appeared, surrounded by his numerous progeny. 他出现时，子女前呼后拥不计其数。', '副词: numerously 名词: numerousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('translucent', '[træns\'luːsnt]', 'adj.半透明的', '1. A translucent design was impressed on the paper. 一个半透明的设计被印在纸上。 2. She is wearing her translucent pajamas. 她穿着半透明的睡衣。', '副词: translucently 名词: translucence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incessantly', '[ɪn\'sesntli]', 'adv.不间断地', '1. The man seemed to be in animal spirits and joked incessantly. 这个人似乎精神很好，他不停地说着笑话。 2. Michael now talks incessantly although not always coherently. 现在已会说话，虽然有时表达不清楚。 3. For ten hours it rained incessantly. 雨不停地下了10个钟头。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bud', '[bʌd]', 'n.芽；花蕾 vi.发芽；萌芽 vt.使发芽', '1. The roses are in bud. 玫瑰花正含苞待放。 2. Summertime bud grafting can be cut take shoot piece, or take xylem shoot less piece, in stock bine dry place decorticates. 夏季芽接可削取芽片,或少带木质部芽片,在砧木茎干处剥皮。 3. The bud developed into a blossom. 花蕾开出了鲜花。 4. The magnolia tree is in bud already. 木兰树已经长出花蕾了。 5. Trees begin to bud in the spring. 树在春天开始发芽。 6. Some flowers bud their leaves very early in spring. 有些花在春季里很早发出叶来。', '名词: budder 过去式: budded 过去分词: budded 现在分词: budding 第三人称单数: buds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imbibe', '[ɪm\'baɪb]', 'v.饮；吸收；吸入', '1. It will imbibe your body with oxygen and help relieve stress. 你将会吸入氧气，帮助自己减压。', '名词: imbiber 过去式: imbibed 过去分词: imbibed 现在分词: imbibing 第三人称单数: imbibes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dumb', '[dʌm]', 'adj.哑的；愚蠢的；不能说话的 vt.使沉默', '1. She\'s been dumb from birth. 她生来就是哑巴。 2. It was dumb of you to say that. 你说那种话真是太愚蠢了。 3. She was unfairly caricatured as a dumb blonde. 她被不公正地丑化成了一个傻头傻脑的金发女郎。 4. He was struck dumb by her sharp question. 他被她那尖锐的问题弄得哑口无言。', '副词: dumbly 比较级: dumber 最高级: dumbest 名词: dumbness 过去式: dumbed 过去分词: dumbed 现在分词: dumbing 第三人称单数: dumbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flat', '[flæt]', 'adj.平坦的；扁平的；单调的；断然的；[音乐]降音的；气不足的 adv.平直地；直截了当；低于标准音高地 n.<英>公寓；平面部分；[音乐]降半音；泄气轮胎 v.变平；降调；住公寓', '1. Most of our county is as flat as a pancake. 我们县大部分地方非常平坦。 2. In flat open country there is plenty of grass for the cattle to feed on. 在开阔平坦的地区有大量的青草供牛群食用。 3. People used to think that the earth was flat. 过去人们认为地球是扁平的。 4. He spoke in a flat monotone. 他说话单调低沉。 5. She lay flat on her back in the warm sunshine. 她在温暖的阳光下平躺著。 6. She is buying a flat close to her office. 她正在购买一套靠近她办公室的单元房。', '副词: flatly 比较级: flatter 最高级: flattest 名词: flatness 过去式: flatted 过去分词: flatted 现在分词: flatting 第三人称单数: flats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instill', '[ɪn\'stɪl]', 'vt.逐渐灌输；滴注', '1. The idea was gradually instilled in the mind of the young prince. 那种思想已逐渐灌输到了年幼的王子的头脑中。 2. Fear of the father is instilled into some children from their infancy. 有的小孩从小就慢慢养成害怕父亲的心理。 3. We must instill a sense of duty in our children. 我们必须在我们的孩子当中灌输一种责任感。 4. The nursery teacher instilled the need for kindness into my children. 幼儿园教师不断地向孩子们灌输仁慈的必要。', '名词: instillation');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plot', '[plɑːt]', 'n.情节；阴谋；图；(小块)土地 v.密谋；绘图；计划；标示位置', '1. The plot thickens. 情节复杂起来了。 2. They are brewing a plot behind the scenes. 他们正在幕后策划一个阴谋。 3. The silly ending robs the plot of any credibility. 这愚蠢的结尾使得整个情节变得一点都不可信。 4. The reporter was killed because he tried to expose a plot. 这名记者因为试图揭露一个阴谋而被杀害。 5. They are plotting how to murder him. 他们在密谋如何杀害他。', '名词: plotlessness 过去式: plotted 过去分词: plotted 现在分词: plotting 第三人称单数: plots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comprehend', '[ˌkɑːmprɪ\'hend]', 'vt.充分理解；领悟；包括', '1. I cannot comprehend this phrase. 我无法理解这个片语。 2. If you can use a word correctly and effectively you comprehend it. 你如果可以正确有效地使用一个词，你就是了解它了。 3. The child couldn\'t comprehend the text. 这孩子不懂该课文的含义。 4. The park comprehends all the land on the other side of the river. 这个公园包括河对岸的所有地方。', '形容词: comprehendible 副词: comprehendingly 过去式: comprehended 过去分词: comprehended 现在分词: comprehending 第三人称单数: comprehends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('minute', '[\'mɪnɪt]', 'n.分钟；片刻；备忘；会议记录 adj.微小的；仔细的 vt.记录', '1. The park is only five minutes from downtown. 这个花园离市中心只有五分钟的路程。 2. Please wait a minute, I\'ll go with you right now. 请等一下,我马上跟你走。 3. She has the habit of making a minute of daily businesses. 她有记录每天各种事务的习惯。 4. He took down the minutes in shorthand. 他将会议记录速记下来。 5. I remembered in minute detail everything that had happened. 我对发生的每件事的细枝末节都记得清清楚楚。 6. Have you minuted what I have just said? 你记下我刚刚说的话了吗？', '名词: minuteness 过去式: minuted 过去分词: minuted 现在分词: minuting 第三人称单数: minutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('carnal', '[\'kɑːrnl]', 'adj.肉体的；世俗的', '1. That is a carnal world. 那是一个肉欲的世界。 2. Love is spiritual, lust is carnal. 爱是精神的，情欲是肉体的。', '副词: carnally 名词: carnality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('isolate', '[\'aɪsəleɪt]', 'vt.使孤立；隔离 adj.孤立的；单独的', '1. We must isolate the handful of enemies to the maximum. 我们要最大限度地孤立一小撮敌人。 2. We should never isolate ourselves from the masses. 我们永远不能脱离群众。 3. The patient should isolate from his child. 这个病人必须立刻和他的孩子隔离。 4. Scientists have isolated the virus causing the epidemic. 科学家们已分离出引起这种流行病的病毒。 5. It would mean inability to close in and isolate him. 这样，就不能把敌人驱逐到狭小的孤立的阵地上去。', '名词: isolator 过去式: isolated 过去分词: isolated 现在分词: isolating 第三人称单数: isolates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lull', '[lʌl]', 'v.使安静；使入睡；哄骗；平息 n.暂停；间歇', '1. The mother lulled the baby to sleep. 母亲哄着孩子入睡了。 2. They lulled me into a false sense of security. 他们哄骗我，让我产生了一种虚假的安全感。 3. During the night the wind lulled. 夜里，风停了。 4. This is just the lull before the storm. 这只是暴风雨前的暂时平静。', '过去式: lulled 过去分词: lulled 现在分词: lulling 第三人称单数: lulls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spectacular', '[spek\'tækjələr]', 'adj.壮观的；令人惊叹的 n.壮观；豪华节目', '1. We watched a spectacular sunset at the beach. 我们在海边欣赏了非常壮观的日落。 2. The view from the top of the tower was spectacular. 从塔顶远眺景色蔚为壮观。 3. The dragon dance in the town square was really spectacular. 城市广场上的舞龙,真是令人叹为观止。 4. Their performance in the championship last night was spectacular. 他们昨晚在锦标赛的表现十分引人注目。 5. We watched a spectacular sunset at the beach. 我们在海边欣赏了非常壮观的日落。', '副词: spectacularly 名词: spectacularity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sapphire', '[\'sæfaɪər]', 'n.蓝宝石；深蓝色 adj.蓝宝石的；深蓝色的', '1. She had the sapphire set in a gold ring. 她把那枚蓝宝石镶在金戒指上了。 2. A first time brooder, a Sapphire Gold xback. 第一次生产的蓝宝石紫蓝底过背。 3. The sapphire is next in hardness to the diamond. 蓝宝石的硬度仅次于钻石。 4. Conclusion Alkali elements have the positive effect on the crystal of sapphire. 结论碱金属元素对山东蓝宝石的结晶有积极的推动作用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abhorrent', '[əb\'hɔːrənt]', 'adj.令人憎恶的', '1. Such an act is abhorrent to my feelings. 这种行为是我所憎恶的。 2. Violence is abhorrent to his gentle nature. 他性情温和，讨厌暴力。', '副词: abhorrently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proficient', '[prə\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.熟练的；精通的 n.能手', '1. He is proficient in English with customer. 他能熟练运用英语与客人交谈。 2. After reading this book, you will be proficient in writing. 读完这本书，你会精于写作。 3. My friend is proficient in three languages. 我的朋友精通三种语言。 4. She was very proficient in music. 她非常精通音乐。 5. He doesn\'t look like a proficient in golf. 他看起来不像是个打高尔夫球的专家。', '副词: proficiently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('utilize', '[\'juːtəlaɪz]', 'vt.<美>利用或使用 =utilise（英）', '1. What criteria do you utilize in selecting employees? 在筛选雇员时你使用什么标准？ 2. In order to utilize land more fully, they adopted close planting. 为了更充分利用土地，他们采取了密植的办法。', '形容词: utilizable 名词: utilization 过去式: utilized 过去分词: utilized 现在分词: utilizing 第三人称单数: utilizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circumstance', '[\'sɜːrkəmstæns]', 'n.环境；详情；事件；(复数)境况', '1. He was forced by the circumstances to do this. 他做此事是为环境所迫。 2. The choice of technique is, therefore, a matter of preference, and in some cases circumstance. 因此,技术的选择是偏好的问题,在某些情况下也与环境有关。 3. I cannot recollect the exact circumstance. 我总是想不起确实的情况。 4. Your arrival was a fortunate circumstance. 你的到来是命中注定的。', '过去式: circumstanced 过去分词: circumstanced 现在分词: circumstancing 第三人称单数: circumstances');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fragrant', '[\'freɪɡrənt]', 'adj.芬香的；馥郁的', '1. The aspic is one kind of strongly fragrant purple blue color floret. 薰衣草是一种馥郁的紫蓝色的小花。 2. Fragrant fruit juice is the best drink to entertain guests in the four seasons. 香气馥郁的果露饮料是四季酬宾美物。', '副词: fragrantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('undergo', '[ˌʌndər\'ɡoʊ]', 'vt.经历；经受；遭受', '1. This city underwent great changes. 这座城市经历了巨大的变化。 2. The castle will undergo extensive and costly renovations. 那城堡要用巨资进行全面整修。 3. Man\'s idea of God would undoubtedly undergo a change if we were to discover other intelligent beings in the universe. 如果我们真的发现宇宙中有其他的智慧生命,人类关于上帝的观念一定会经历一场变化。 4. I hope that I shall never again have to undergo such unpleasant experience. 我希望我永远不会再遭遇到这种不愉快的经历。', '过去式: underwent 过去分词: undergone 现在分词: undergoing 第三人称单数: undergoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nearly', '[\'nɪrli]', 'adv.几乎；差不多；密切地', '1. Nearly all of them kept aloof from such doctrines. 他们几乎都不接受这种教条。 2. That fever nearly finished him off. 那场热病几乎送了他的命。 3. He plays golf nearly every weekend. 他差不多每个周末都打高尔夫球。 4. They sat so close that their heads nearly touched. 他们坐得那么近，头都差不多碰到一起了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('endangered', '[ɪn\'deɪndʒəd]', 'adj.濒于灭绝的 动词endanger的过去式和过去分词.', '1. This rare bird has become an endangered species. 这种珍禽已成为濒临灭绝的物种。 2. We should do our best to save endangered species. 我们应该竭尽全力挽救濒于灭绝的生物。 3. Scientists think that the Arctic is endangered by pollution. 科学家们认为北极面临着被污染的危险。 4. The oil spill endangered thousands of birds. 石油的溢泄危及成千上万的鸟儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convince', '[kən\'vɪns]', 'vt.使确信；使信服；说服', '1. I try to convince him of the reality of the danger. 我试图使他相信危险的确存在。 2. It took many hours to convince me of his guilt. 研究了许多个小时我才相信他有罪。 3. He convinced me of his sincerity. 他使我确信他的真诚。 4. There was not an atom of evidence to convince him. 没有一点能使他信服的证据。', '形容词: convincible 名词: convincement 过去式: convinced 过去分词: convinced 现在分词: convincing 第三人称单数: convinces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incur', '[ɪn\'kɜːr]', 'vt.招致；遭受；惹起', '1. Your despite at him will incur his revenge. 他会因你的藐视态度而报复你的。 2. If you don\'t do the job properly, you will incur blame. 如果你不把工作做好,你将会招人责难。 3. A slowdown in the economy caused us to incur great losses. 经济的减缓使我们遭受了很大的损失。 4. He incurred substantial losses during the stock market crash. 他在股市猛跌时蒙受了巨大的损失。', '过去式: incurred 过去分词: incurred 现在分词: incurring 第三人称单数: incurs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ecosystem', '[\'iːkoʊsɪstəm]', 'n.生态系统', '1. Water is the core of a healthy ecosystem. 水是维持生态系统良性循环的根本。 2. Research Review on Wetland Ecosystem Health. 湿地生态系统健康研究进展。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detective', '[dɪ\'tektɪv]', 'n.侦探 adj.侦探的', '1. The detective laid great stress on details. 侦探特别强调细节。 2. The detective was trying to ascertain exactly who was at the party. 这个侦探试图查明都有谁参加了聚会。 3. The detective thought the stick was relative to the murder case. 侦探认为这根木棒和谋杀案有牵连。 4. The detective tried to reason out how the thief had escaped. 这个侦探反复琢磨想弄明白那个窃贼是怎样逃跑的。 5. She read detective stories as an escape. 她看侦探小说解闷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bar', '[bɑːr]', 'n.酒吧；条；横木；栅 vt.禁止；阻挠；闩上；在 ... 设栅栏', '1. There are several bars in the hotel. 这家旅馆里有好几个酒吧。 2. A bar of chocolate is enough to stop his crying. 一条巧克力就可以让他不哭了。 3. There\'s a strong bar on the door. 门上有一个很坚固的闩。 4. There is a burning man hovering in the air over a grille in the Smoldering Corpse Bar. 有一个焚烧中的人，飘浮在冒烟尸体酒吧的铁栅上方。 5. After the bombing, the whole area was barred to the public. 轰炸后，整个地区禁止公众通行。', '过去式: barred 过去分词: barred 现在分词: barring 第三人称单数: bars');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('depend', '[dɪ\'pend]', 'vi.依赖；依靠；取决于', '1. Children depend on their parents for food and clothing. 小孩依赖他们的父母供给衣食。 2. He is a man whom you can depend on. 他是个你可以信赖的人。 3. The country depends heavily on its tourist trade. 这个国家的经济在很大程度上依靠其旅游业。 4. I have no one but you to depend on. 除了你，我没有可依靠的人。', '过去式: depended 过去分词: depended 现在分词: depending 第三人称单数: depends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wagon', '[\'wæɡən]', 'n.四轮马车；货车 v.用四轮马车运', '1. He harnessed the horse to a wagon. 他把马套到四轮马车上。 2. An ox pulls a wagon into the village. 有只牛拉着一台四轮车进入村庄。 3. The old wagon rattled down the road. 破旧的四轮运货马车喀嚓喀嚓地行进在路上。 4. His wagon was smashed into kindling wood. 他的货车撞得稀烂。 5. They wagoned the goods to the market. 他们用四轮马车把货物运到市场。', '过去式: wagoned 过去分词: wagoned 现在分词: wagoning 第三人称单数: wagons');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indomitable', '[ɪn\'dɑːmɪtəbl]', 'adj.不屈不挠的', '1. He is endowed with indomitable will. 他有不屈不挠的意志。 2. I really admire her indomitable optimism and can-do spirit. 我实在佩服她不屈不挠的乐观态度和苦干的精神。', '副词: indomitably 名词: indomitability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('peak', '[piːk]', 'n.尖端；山顶；顶峰 v.达到顶峰；使处于顶点 vi.消瘦', '1. In Yersa I noticed a spike on the peak of the pyramid-shaped roof of a church. 在叶拉萨村,我发现一座教堂的金字塔屋顶的尖端有一颗尖钉。 2. The mountain peaks are covered with snow all year. 山顶上终年积雪。 3. Many mountaineers have reached that mountain peak. 许多登山家都登上过那座大山的顶峰。 4. Tourism is at its peak in August. 旅游业在八月份达到高峰。 5. Primary school enrolment will peak this year. 今年小学入学人数将达到最高峰。', '过去式: peaked 过去分词: peaked 现在分词: peaking 第三人称单数: peaks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('escort', '[\'eskɔːrt]', 'n.护送者；护航舰；陪伴者；陪游；妓女 vt.护送；陪伴', '1. He offered to be her escort, but she declined it. 他提出护送她，但她谢绝了。 2. The government provided an armed escort for the visiting head of State. 政府为到访的元首派出了武装卫队。 3. He is the commander in chief of this escort ,and he holds great power. 他是这艘护航舰的总指挥，权利很大。 4. The Queen\'s yacht had an escort of ten destroyers. 有十艘驱逐舰为女王的游艇护航. 5. He will escort you through the forest. 他护送你穿过森林。', '过去式: escorted 过去分词: escorted 现在分词: escorting 第三人称单数: escorts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compatible', '[kəm\'pætəbl]', 'adj.一致的；兼容的；适合的 n.兼容', '1. The proposed new regulation is not compatible with the existing policy. 提出的新规定与现有的政策不符。 2. We should remain the compatible family relationships. 我们应该维持和谐的家庭关系。 3. He and his wife are not compatible 他跟他的妻子合不来。 4. It may not be compatible with your version of Mac OS X. 它可能与您的Mac OS X版本不兼容。 5. He drove a car at a speed compatible with safety. 他以安全速度行车。', '副词: compatibly 名词: compatibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inverse', '[ˌɪn\'vɜːrs]', 'adj.倒转的；相反的 n.倒数；相反的事物；(数学)逆反函数；负数', '1. Subtraction is the inverse operation of addition. 减法是加法的逆运算。 2. When you define certain operators, Visual Basic requires that you also define the operator for the inverse operation. 当定义某些特定的运算符时,Visual Basic还要求定义该运算符的逆运算。 3. The inverse of its slope is the speed of light. 其倾斜的倒数是光速。 4. The logarithmic function is defined as the inverse of the exponential function. 对数函数是作为指数函数的反函数来定义的。', '副词: inversely');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proscribe', '[proʊ\'skraɪb]', 'v.禁止；放逐；排斥；剥夺…的公权', '1. The sale of narcotics is proscribed by law. 法律禁止贩卖毒品。', '名词: proscriber 过去式: proscribed 过去分词: proscribed 现在分词: proscribing 第三人称单数: proscribes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('connoisseur', '[ˌkɒnə\'sɜː]', 'n.鉴识家；内行', '1. He is a connoisseur of antique furniture. 他是古家俱鉴定家。 2. Only the real connoisseur could tell the difference between these two wines. 只有真正的内行才能指出这两种酒的区别。', '名词: connoisseurship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('geology', '[dʒi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.地质学；（某地区的）地质情况；地质学的著作', '1. I know only a few streaks about geology. 我对地质学只是略知一二。 2. Geology is the science of the earth\'s history. 地质学是研究地球历史的科学。 3. The students went to study the geology of that region. 学生们去研究那个地区的地质情况。 4. It\'s essentially a mimic of the natural process of geology on a smaller time scale. 它实际上是对地质情况自然过程的一个模拟，只是时间更短。', '形容词: geologic 副词: geologically 名词: geologist 名词复数: geologies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rupture', '[\'rʌptʃər]', 'n.破裂；断裂；[医]疝气 v.（使）破裂', '1. The negotiation came to a rupture. 谈判破裂了。 2. He died of a rupture of blood-vessels. 他血管破裂而死。 3. Failure of the machine may be caused by the rupture of the triangle belt. 这台机器的故障可能是由三角带断裂引起的。 4. I nearly gave myself a rupture lifting that pile of books. 提那一大堆书差点儿让我得了疝气。 5. He\'ll rupture a muscle if he goes on dancing like that! 他要是继续那样跳舞，会跳得皮开肉裂！', '形容词: rupturable 过去式: ruptured 过去分词: ruptured 现在分词: rupturing 第三人称单数: ruptures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compassion', '[kəm\'pæʃn]', 'n.怜悯；同情', '1. I had compassion for him. 我怜悯他。 2. He teaches us to have compassion on the poor. 他教导我们对穷人应有怜悯心。 3. Compassion is a sign of weakness. 怜悯是弱者的标志。 4. I should not have compassion for those lofty birds. 我不会怜悯这些高贵的鸟。', '形容词: compassionless');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('magnitude', '[\'mæɡnɪtuːd]', 'n.大小；重要；光度；（地震）级数；（星星）等级', '1. I want to know the magnitude of this equipment. 我想知道这个设备的大小。 2. The magnitude of the epidemic was frightening. 这种流行病传播范围之广令人惶惶不安。 3. I had not realized the magnitude of the problem. 我没意识到这个问题的重要性。 4. The main quake was estimated at magnitude 6.6. 据估计主震区的震级有6.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immerse', '[ɪ\'mɜːrs]', 'vt.浸；陷入', '1. I immerse my clothes in the water. 我把衣服浸在水里。 2. Please immerse the plant in water for a few minutes. 把那棵植物在水里浸泡几分钟。 3. He immersed himself totally in his work. 他埋头于工作。 4. I immerse myself into reciting English vocabulary. 我专心于背英语词汇。', '过去式: immersed 过去分词: immersed 现在分词: immersing 第三人称单数: immerses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forefront', '[\'fɔːrfrʌnt]', 'n.最前列；最前线', '1. Women have always been at the forefront of the Green movement. 妇女总是在环境保护运动的最前列。 2. And China is at the forefront of research and development in herbal medicines. 而中国正处于草药研究和开发的最前沿。 3. The brave soldier was in the forefront of the fighting. 那个勇敢的士兵战斗在最前线。 4. We said that the youth ought to stand in the forefront of the times. 我们说过,年轻人应该站在时代的最前线。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tundra', '[\'tʌndrə]', 'n.苔原；冻土地带', '1. Gley soils are typical of tundra, meadows, and boggy areas. 灰黏土是苔原、草地以及沼地所特有的。 2. In the north are vast stretches of icy, treeless tundra. 北部为冰天雪地的没有树木的辽阔平原，称之为冻原带。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elasticity', '[ˌiːlæ\'stɪsəti]', 'n.弹力；弹性；伸缩性；灵活性', '1. Elasticity of fluids is not subject to simple measurement at present. 目前液体的弹力不能根据简单的测量而定。 2. His voice has a good elasticity. 他的声音很有弹性。 3. The skin eventually loses its elasticity. 皮肤最终会失去弹性。 4. My life is full of elasticity and possibility! 我的生命充满弹性与无限可能。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('Gothic', '[\'ɡɑːθɪk]', 'adj.哥特式小说风格的 n.哥特式小说、电影或戏剧 Gothic: 哥特式的； 哥特人的； 哥特语的； 中世纪的； 野蛮的； 粗鄙的. Gothic：哥特式； 哥特语； 黑体字.', '1. This article is printed in Gothic. 这篇文章是用粗黑体字印刷的。', '副词: Gothically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('converge', '[kən\'vɜːrdʒ]', 'vi.聚合；集中；会聚 vt.使集合', '1. The roads converge just before the station. 四面八方的道路会聚在火车站前。 2. These lines converge at a certain point. 这些线集中于某一点。 3. If you look at the end of your nose, your eyes converge. 如果你看着你的鼻尖，你的两眼就向一点集中。 4. In this case the rays obviously do not converge. 此时，光线显然不会聚。', '过去式: converged 过去分词: converged 现在分词: converging 第三人称单数: converges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('notorious', '[noʊ\'tɔːriəs]', 'adj.臭名昭著的', '1. He is notorious for his goings-on. 他因行为不检点而声名狼藉。 2. The district is notorious for its fogs. 那地区以浓雾出名。 3. Hitler is a notorious dictator. 希特勒是一个臭名昭著的独裁者。 4. The notorious thief will be put up for trial next week. 那个臭名昭著的偷窃犯将于下周出庭受审。', '副词: notoriously 名词: notoriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idle', '[\'aɪdl]', 'adj.无目的；无聊的; 懒惰的；闲散的; 无根据的 vt.虚度; 使空闲 vi.不作事；闲逛; (机器)空转', '1. Being at an idle end,we often go to and look around the shops. 闲来无事，我们常去逛逛商店。 2. Idle folks have the least leisure. 懒惰的人最没空闲。 3. No matter how rich, one shall not live an idle life. 不管一个人多么富有,都不应该过着闲散的生活。 4. I never believe idle reports. 我从来不信捕风捉影的传闻。 5. The strike idled many workers. 罢工使许多工人没事干。 6. I hate you to idle about. 我不喜欢你游手好闲。', '副词: idly 比较级: idler 最高级: idlest 名词: idleness 过去式: idled 过去分词: idled 现在分词: idling 第三人称单数: idles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attainment', '[ə\'teɪnmənt]', 'n.达到；获得 （常复数）attainments:成就； 才能； 学识.', '1. He was far from the attainment of this object. 他远未达到自己的目标。 2. Thatwill help lead you to the attainment of your goals. 那会有助于你达到目标。 3. The attainment of wealth did not make her happy. 获得财富并没有使她幸福。 4. You may well have to forego wealth and power if you want to assure the attainment of happiness and freedom. 如果你想要确保快乐与自由的获得，你可就得放开财富与权力。 5. Prof. Thomson is one scholar of the highest attainment. 汤姆生教授是一位学识渊博的学者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confess', '[kən\'fes]', 'v.承认；供认；告解；听取忏悔', '1. I confess you are right on one point. 我承认你在某一点上是正确的。 2. Now, I must confess that I\'m at my wit\'s end. 现在我必须承认我已毫无办法。 3. He confessed that he had never seen her before. 他承认以前从未见过她。 4. He refused to confess to his crime. 他拒绝认罪。', '形容词: confessable 副词: confessedly 过去式: confessed 过去分词: confessed 现在分词: confessing 第三人称单数: confesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annually', '[\'ænjuəli]', 'adv.每年；年年', '1. They celebrate their wedding anniversary annually. 他们每年庆祝一番结婚纪念日。 2. We must harness the rivers which overflow annually. 我们必须治理那些每年泛滥的河流。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intact', '[ɪn\'tækt]', 'adj.完好无缺的；原封不动的；未经触碰的', '1. Despite his misfortunes, his faith and optimism remained intact. 虽然他遭到一连串的不幸，他的信心和乐观丝毫未减。 2. You may have your money back on this woolen sweater if it is kept clean and intact. 如果羊毛衫保持清洁、完好无缺，您可以退款。 3. The money was returned intact by its finder. 钱原封未动地被捡拾者送还。 4. This stretch of wetlands has remained intact. 这块湿地一直保持着自然的面貌。', '副词: intactly 名词: intactness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('handle', '[\'hændl]', 'v.处理；对待；操作；触；买卖 n.把手；柄', '1. I was impressed by her handling of the affair. 我觉得她对此事的处理很了不起。 2. The speaker was roughly handled by the mob. 演说者受到暴民的粗暴对待。 3. He\'s not a very good teacher---he doesn\'t know how to handle children. 他不是一个好的老师---他不懂得如何对待孩子。 4. He knows how to handle the machine. 他会操作这台机器。 5. I turned the handle and opened the door. 我转了转拉手,把门打开。', '形容词: handleless 过去式: handled 过去分词: handled 现在分词: handling 第三人称单数: handles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exit', '[\'eksɪt]', 'n.出口；退场 v.离去；退出', '1. She made a dart for the exit. 她冲向出口。 2. At the roundabout, take the third exit. 在环状交叉路口，从第三条出路驶出。 3. I was eventually granted an exit visa. 我终于获得了出境签证。 4. He made a quick exit to avoid meeting her. 他迅速离去以避免见到她。', '过去式: exited 过去分词: exited 现在分词: exiting 第三人称单数: exits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('switch', '[swɪtʃ]', 'n.转换；开关；鞭子 v.改变；交换；转换；鞭打', '1. How do I switch to the next major release branch? 如何转换为下个主要发布版本分支？ 2. The current will switch over after I push this button. 我按下这个按钮之后，电流会被转换。 3. I wish to turn on the light, where is the switch? 我想要开亮那一支电灯,请问开关在哪儿? 4. The father whipped his child with a switch. 父亲用鞭子抽打他的孩子。 5. No, hold it a second, switch that to roast chicken. 不，等一等，把那个换成烤子鸡。', '形容词: switchable 名词: switcher 过去式: switched 过去分词: switched 现在分词: switching 第三人称单数: switches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('Babylonian', '[ˌbæbəˈloʊniən]', 'n.巴比伦人；巴比伦语 adj.巴比伦的；奢侈的', '1. They differ from the Ashkenazi Jews in their traditional language, Ladino, and in their preservation of Babylonian rather than Palestinian Jewish ritual traditions. 与德系犹太人不同之处在于他们使用自己的传统语言拉迪诺语，并且持守巴比伦犹太教传统而不依循巴勒斯坦犹太教传统。 2. The Babylonian captivity civilized them and consolidated them. 巴比伦的囚虏使他们走向文明，并且统一起来。 3. A great literary revival followed the recovery of Babylonian independence. 随着巴比伦的独立，一场极大的文学复苏运动随之而来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grind', '[ɡraɪnd]', 'v.磨；压迫；碾碎；磨得吱吱响；逐渐停顿 n.苦事；磨；碾', '1. It won\'t grind down any finer than this. 不能磨得比这个再细了。 2. Some people grind their teeth while they are asleep. 有些人睡觉时磨牙齿。 3. People in this area were ground down by hunger and poverty. 这个地区的人们受着饥饿和贫穷的折磨。 4. We grind up the wheat to make flour. 我们把小麦磨成面粉。 5. Marking examination papers is a real grind. 批改试卷的确是个苦事。', '副词: grindingly 过去式: ground 过去分词: ground 现在分词: grinding 第三人称单数: grinds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chilled', '[tʃɪld]', 'adj.冷却的；冷藏的；寒冷的 动词chill的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He had finished the tall glass of chilled fresh orange juice. 他又喝了一大杯清凉的鲜桔子汁。 2. Chilled water coil are controlled in much the same way as heating. 冷水盘管的控热和加热盘管的差不多相同。 3. This wine is best served chilled. 这种葡萄酒最好冷饮。 4. White wine should be slightly chilled. 白葡萄酒应稍微冰一下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('engine', '[\'endʒɪn]', 'n.发动机；引擎；机车；火车头 vt.给 ... 装引擎', '1. What\'s the cubic capacity of this engine? 这台发动机的立体容积是多少？ 2. There must be something wrong with the engine of my car. 我汽车的引擎一定是出故障了。 3. Industrialization is the most important engine of economic growth. 工业化是经济增长最重要的拉动因素。 4. There was a puff of steam from the engine before it stopped. 机车喷出一股蒸气后就停了下来。', '过去式: engined 过去分词: engined 现在分词: engining 第三人称单数: engines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('editorial', '[ˌedɪ\'tɔːriəl]', 'n.社论 adj.编辑的', '1. The editorial lashed out at official corruption. 那篇社论猛烈抨击官场的腐败。 2. He recomposed the editorial till dawn. 他改写社论直到天亮。 3. She has editorial control over what is included. 她有权决定编辑的内容。 4. To this moment, generally speaking, editorial anger vanished completely, absolutely won\'t reintroduce what is other requirement. 到这个时候，一般来说，编辑的愤怒就烟消云散了，绝不会再提出什么别的要求。', '副词: editorially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('categorical', '[ˌkætə\'ɡɔːrɪkl]', 'adj.绝对的；分类的', '1. The judgement was harsh and categorical. 这个说法是够尖刻的，够干脆的。 2. He has gone wiggle-waggle and cannot be persuaded to categorical. 他犹豫不决，无法劝他持明确的态度。 3. A categorical arrangement of specimens is needed to show the visitors. 需要标本的分类排列展示给访问者看。', '副词: categorically 异体字: categoric 名词: categoricalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('improvise', '[\'ɪmprəvaɪz]', 'v.即兴创作；即兴表演；临时准备', '1. Akel says this style of acting required the crew to improvise as well. 称这种演出方式要求剧组人员都要即兴创作。 2. It is much easier to improvise a song than it is to improvise a symphony. 即兴创作一支歌曲比即兴创作一部交响曲要简单得多。', '名词: improviser 过去式: improvised 过去分词: improvised 现在分词: improvising 第三人称单数: improvises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('march', '[mɑːrtʃ]', 'n.行军；行进；游行示威；稳步前进；进行曲 v.行进；前进；进发；使同行；游行示威 March n.三月', '1. Not a single man fell out in the long march. 在长途行军中没有一个人掉队。 2. The army was now on the march to Shanghai. 部队当时正向上海进军。 3. Science is on the march. 科学正在进步中。 4. The peace march attracted a large turnout. 和平游行吸引了大量的参加者。 5. The shower being over, we continued to march. 阵雨过去之后我们继续行进。 6. This term will begin on March 1st. 这个学期三月一日开始。', '过去式: marched 过去分词: marched 现在分词: marching 第三人称单数: marches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('privilege', '[\'prɪvəlɪdʒ]', 'n.特权；荣幸；特别恩典；基本人权 vt.给特权；免除', '1. I had the privilege of meeting the queen. 我有会见王后的特权。 2. It is a great privilege to know you. 认识你是一件难得的事。 3. It was a privilege to work with him. 和他在一起工作是一项殊荣。 4. Kings cannot privilege what God forbade. 国王不能原谅上帝不允许做的事。', '过去式: privileged 过去分词: privileged 现在分词: privileging 第三人称单数: privileges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infer', '[ɪn\'fɜːr]', 'vt.推断；猜测；暗示 vi.作出推论', '1. We can infer the meaning of the word in the context. 我们可以从上下文中推断这个词的含义。 2. They infer a conclusion from the facts. 他们从事实中推断出结论。 3. I infer that my proposal has been accepted. 我推测我的建议已被接受。 4. Ragged clothing infers poverty. 衣衫褴褛意味着贫困。 5. We can infer from his expression that he is frustrated. 我们可以从他的表情中推断出他很沮丧。', '形容词: inferable 副词: inferably 名词: inferrer 过去式: inferred 过去分词: inferred 现在分词: inferring 第三人称单数: infers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('simultaneously', '[ˌsaɪməl\'teɪnjəsli]', 'adv.同时地', '1. The event will be telecast simultaneously to nearly 150 cities. 这一盛事将向近150个城市同时进行电视广播。 2. This machine can sew and cut the fabric simultaneously. 这台机器可以一边缝纫,一边裁布,同时运作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('secrete', '[sɪ\'kriːt]', 'vt.隐藏；隐匿 vt.分泌', '1. He found the money secreted in a drawer. 他找到了藏在抽屉里的钱。 2. Squirrels secrete a supply of nuts for winter. 松鼠为准备过冬而藏坚果。 3. He secreted himself to avoid being caught. 他为了躲避追捕，隐匿起来了。 4. The kidneys secrete urine. 肾脏是分泌尿液的器官。', '过去式: secreted 过去分词: secreted 现在分词: secreting 第三人称单数: secretes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prior', '[\'praɪər]', 'adj.优先的；在前的；更重要的 adv.居先；在前', '1. He feels a prior obligation to his job as a journalist. 他觉得要优先为他的新闻记者的工作尽职。 2. Generally speaking, individuals who first appropriate part of a water supply have prior claim over those whose appropriation is later in time. 一般来说，先使用水资源的人比后使用者拥有更优先的权利。 3. The offer is subject to prior sale. 该报盘以未售出前为准。 4. His answer was tinted by his prior knowledge. 他的回答说明他先前就有所了解。 5. The golden octave holds within it all of the prior eight vibrations or planes within its field. 金色音阶内掌握着所有在前的八度音阶或它场内所有的层面。', '副词: priorly 名词: priority');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vegetation', '[ˌvedʒə\'teɪʃn]', 'n.植物；草木；(植物)生长；【医】赘生物，赘疣，增殖体', '1. Coal is carbonized and lithifyied vegetation. 煤由植物碳化及石化所成。 2. The lush vegetation spoke of a damper climate here. 茂盛的植物说明这里的气候是潮湿的。 3. The hills are covered in lush green vegetation. 这片丘岭草木茂盛，郁郁葱葱。 4. This place is desolate of all vegetation. 这个地方不长草木。', '形容词: vegetational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abbreviate', '[ə\'briːvieɪt]', 'vt.缩写；缩短；使简略', '1. In writing, the title `Doctor\' is abbreviated to `Dr\'. 在书写时，Doctor头衔的缩写是Dr. 2. It is seldom acceptable to abbreviate words in formal writing. 在正式的书面语中使用缩写语通常是不能接受的。 3. The teacher asked me to abbreviate my report to one page . 老师让我把报告缩短为一页。 4. The United States of america is commonly abbreviated to U.S.a.. 美利坚合众国常被缩略为 U.', '名词: abbreviator 过去式: abbreviated 过去分词: abbreviated 现在分词: abbreviating 第三人称单数: abbreviates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lash', '[læʃ]', 'n.鞭子；鞭打；睫毛；讽刺 v.鞭打；摆动；抨击', '1. By rod and lash, the boy was punished. 木棍和鞭子用来惩罚这个男孩。 2. The pirate captain beat his crew with a lash. 海盗船长用鞭子抽打他的船员。 3. With a lash of its tail the tiger leaped at her. 老虎把尾巴一甩朝她扑过来。 4. Does the Lash Extender come in other colors apart from black ? 睫毛增长液除黑色外，还有什么其它颜色？ 5. He began to lash Luke unmercifully across buttocks and thighs. 他开始无情地鞭打卢克的屁股和大腿。', '过去式: lashed 过去分词: lashed 现在分词: lashing 第三人称单数: lashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jar', '[dʒɑːr]', 'n.广口瓶；坛子；刺耳声；震动 vi.发刺耳声；不协调；震荡；冲突 vt.扰乱；震动', '1. I can\'t get the lid off this jar. 我打不开这广口瓶的盖子。 2. The jar contains ten glasses of water. 这只大口瓶能装十杯水。 3. I need a jar to make the krauts. 我需要一个坛子做泡菜。 4. He fashioned the clay into a jar. 他用粘土做成一个陶土罐子。 5. The iron gate jarred when he opened it. 他开门时，铁门发出刺耳的嘎嘎声。 6. The children\'s screams jar my nerves. 孩子们的尖叫声使我神经不安。', '副词: jarringly 名词: jarful 过去式: jarred 过去分词: jarred 现在分词: jarring 第三人称单数: jars');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manage', '[\'mænɪdʒ]', 'v.管理；经营；做成；设法对付；提供；有空', '1. He managed the company when his father was away. 他父亲离开的时候,由他管理公司。 2. The success of the restaurant lies in that it is well managed. 这个餐厅的成功在于它的完善经营。 3. I shall be able to manage it without help. 我一个人能行。 4. His wife knows how to manage him when he is angry. 他的妻子知道在他生气时怎么对付他。', '过去式: managed 过去分词: managed 现在分词: managing 第三人称单数: manages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assist', '[ə\'sɪst]', 'vt.帮助；协助 vi.帮助；出席 n.帮助；协助；助攻；协助的器械', '1. A team of nurses assisted the doctor in performing the operation. 一组护士协助医生施行手术。 2. I saw the angels standing near us, waiting to assist us, rejoicing in our accomplishments and joys. 我看见天使站在我们旁边,等着帮助我们,为我们的成就及喜悦而欢呼。 3. Sixty years ago, George Marshall came to this commencement and announced a plan to assist the nations of post-war Europe. 六十年前，乔治·马歇尔也是在这个地方的毕业典礼上，宣布了一个计划，帮助那些欧洲国家的战后建设。 4. I have too much work and no one to assist me 我工作太多,又没人协助我 5. I assisted in doing his homework. 我帮助他做功课。 6. The victims of earthquake need assist asap. 那些地震灾民需要立即援助。', '名词: assister 过去式: assisted 过去分词: assisted 现在分词: assisting 第三人称单数: assists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('induce', '[ɪn\'duːs]', 'vt.引起；促使；劝服；引诱', '1. The medicine will induce sleep. 这种药会引起睡意。 2. They hoped their work would induce social changes. 他们希望自己的工作可以引起社会上的某些变化。 3. I can\'t think what induced her to marry him. 我想不出到底是什么原因促使她嫁给他。 4. Alcohol can induce a loosening of the tongue. 酒精可使人信口开河。', '形容词: inducible 过去式: induced 过去分词: induced 现在分词: inducing 第三人称单数: induces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dinosaur', '[\'daɪnəsɔːr]', 'n.恐龙 n.(俚)过时、落伍的人或事物', '1. The blue whale is bigger than the biggest dinosaur. 蓝鲸比最大的恐龙还要大。 2. We reconstructed what the dinosaur looked like from a few of its bones. 我们根据恐龙的一些骨头重组恐龙的原貌。 3. His movie of the extinction of dinosaurs was a great success. 他的关于恐龙灭绝的电影取得了巨大的成功。', '形容词: dinosauric');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pungent', '[\'pʌndʒənt]', 'adj.刺鼻的；辛辣的；尖锐的；刻薄的', '1. With less fat to balance out the pungent flavors, you can really taste the natural piquancy of lush spring fields. 以少量的脂肪来平衡辛辣的香草味，你能真正品尝到春天郁郁葱葱的野外所特有的自然辛辣味。 2. The president was shocked because he received an anonymous letter which contained some pungent problems. 总统收到了一封匿名信，里面有一些很尖锐的问题，这让他感到很震惊。 3. Yet it breeds antipathies of the most pungent character between those who lay the emphasis differently. 然而，由于个人的着重点不同，彼此之间就产生了许多非常尖锐的嫌恶感。', '副词: pungently 名词: pungency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meager', '[\'miːgə]', 'adj.贫乏的；不足的；瘦的', '1. It was medieval European monks who introduced scientific brewing techniques in an effort to produce a nutritious beverage to supplement their meager diets. 正是中世纪欧洲的僧侣们引进科学的啤酒酿造技术，制造有营养的饮料，从而补充了他们贫乏的饮食。', '副词: meagerly 名词: meagerness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pigeon', '[\'pɪdʒɪn]', 'n.鸽子', '1. A pigeon perched on our porch railing. 一只鸽子栖息在我们门廊的栏杆上。 2. Little pigeon can carry great message. 鸽子虽小，大事可传。 3. A pigeon is cooing up in one of the elm. 一只鸽子在榆树上咕咕地叫。 4. An old man sat on the park bench and fed the pigeon. 一位老人坐在公园的长凳上喂鸽子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vanity', '[\'vænəti]', 'n.自负；虚荣心；无价值的东西；浮华', '1. Vanity is his Achilles\' heel. 虚荣自负是他的致命伤。 2. He has many faults, but vanity is not one of them. 他有很多缺点，但并没有虚荣心。 3. His vanity brought his downfall. 他因虚荣心太重而垮台。 4. She married the rich man out of vanity. 她出于虚荣心而嫁给了那个富人。', '名词复数: vanities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('observance', '[əb\'zɜːrvəns]', 'n.遵守；仪式；纪念', '1. The worker was praised for his observance of the rules. 这个工人因为严格遵守规则而受到了表扬。 2. The company holds its people to strict observance of that code. 公司要求所属人员严格遵守那项规章制度。 3. The speaker advocated a less austere observance of the Sabbath. 演讲者倡导放宽安息日的严格规定。 4. For this reason they are tolerated in the observance of their rites. 所以犹太人是被容许举行他们的宗教仪式的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accomplished', '[ə\'kɑːmplɪʃt]', 'adj.完成的；有成就的；娴熟的；有造诣的；有教养的 动词accomplish的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Openings and closings were all accomplished with majestic rituality. 开幕和闭幕都是用隆重的仪式来完成的。 2. John is an accomplished scholar. 约翰是个有成就的学者。 3. Together this series is among the most moving and accomplished autobiographies-in-paint. 总的来讲，这一系列中的作品属于销售量最好以及手笔最娴熟的自传体油画。 4. She is an accomplished performer. 她是一个很有造诣的表演者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instruct', '[ɪn\'strʌkt]', 'v.教；命令；指导；[计] 指示', '1. His uncle instructed him in French. 他的叔叔教他法语。 2. Don\'t instruct your secretary to say you are out when you are in. 不要教你的秘书在你在的时候说不在。 3. It does not pertain to the young to instruct their elders. 年轻人不应该对老年人发号施令。 4. Please instruct me how to do my work. 请指导一下我如何工作。', '过去式: instructed 过去分词: instructed 现在分词: instructing 第三人称单数: instructs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shrimp', '[ʃrɪmp]', 'n.虾；瘦小的人（物） vi.钓虾', '1. The fried shrimp has not been cooked through yet. 这炸虾里面没有熟。 2. You can catch over a hundred pounds of shrimp. 你一次就能捕到上百磅的虾。 3. He is a shrimp of a boy, about six years old. 他是个六岁左右的小家伙。 4. They will go shrimping this afternoon. 今天下午他们去钓小虾。', '名词: shrimper 名词复数: shrimp 过去式: shrimped 过去分词: shrimped 现在分词: shrimping 第三人称单数: shrimps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('facetious', '[fə\'siːʃəs]', 'adj.（常为不当地）引人发笑的；诙谐的', '1. He is so facetious that he turns everything into a joke. 他好开玩笑，把一切都变成戏谑。 2. I became angry with the little boy at his facetious remarks. 我对那小男孩的玩笑话感到生气。 3. Facetious remarks are part of his stock-in-trade. 讲俏皮话是他的拿手好戏。', '副词: facetiously 名词: facetiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('screen', '[skriːn]', 'n.屏幕；银幕；隔板；屏风；掩蔽物；纱窗；纱门；筛子 v.掩蔽；包庇；放映；筛；检查', '1. The advertisement is full of the TV screen today. 今天，电视屏幕被广告占据。 2. Buzz suddenly appeared on my computer screen. 巴兹突然出现在我的电脑屏幕上。 3. Familiar scenes were imaged on the screen. 银幕上映出了熟悉的景象。 4. Someday I will be a star on the big screen. 有一天我将成为大银幕上的明星。 5. The curtains screen out the sunlight. 窗帘遮住了阳光。', '形容词: screenable 名词: screener 过去式: screened 过去分词: screened 现在分词: screening 第三人称单数: screens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commentary', '[\'kɑːmənteri]', 'n.实况报道；现场解说；评论；注释', '1. His running commentary on the football match was excellent. 他对这次足球赛所作的实况报道十分精彩。 2. Tours have live English commentary. 旅游配有现场英语解说。 3. We\'d better not make any commentary on others. 我们最好不要评论他人。 4. I think his commentary on this issue is not correct. 我认为他对这个问题的评论是不正确的。', '形容词: commentarial 名词复数: commentaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appear', '[ə\'pɪr]', 'vi.出现；出版；显得；好像；登场', '1. A ship appeared on the horizon. 船出现在水平线上。 2. His book appears on the market. 他的书出版了。 3. An article about him appeared in the paper. 一篇有关他的文章在报上发表。 4. She appeared very confident. 她显得很自信。', '过去式: appeared 过去分词: appeared 现在分词: appearing 第三人称单数: appears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cease', '[siːs]', 'v.终止；停止 n.停止', '1. He was going to cease working for them. 他将不再为他们干活。 2. When can we cease from our labours? 我们什么时候才能免除劳役之苦? 3. The old man ceased breathing the night before. 老人前一天晚上停止了呼吸。 4. The newspaper had ceased publication. 报纸已停刊。 5. We worked without cease to get the project finished on time. 我们不停地生产以便按时完成计划', '过去式: ceased 过去分词: ceased 现在分词: ceasing 第三人称单数: ceases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sustained', '[sə\'steɪnd]', 'adj.持久的；经久不衰的 动词sustain的过去式和过去分词.', '1. They failed despite their sustained efforts. 尽管他们不懈地努力, 结果还是失败了。 2. Fiscal revenue of local governments kept sustained and rapid growth. 地方财政收入持续高速增长。 3. The national economy has maintained a sustained, rapid and sound development. 国民经济持续快速健康发展。 4. Hope alone sustained him in his struggle. 在奋斗中，只有希望支持着他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('institute', '[\'ɪnstɪtuːt]', 'n.学院；学会；协会 vt.开始；制定；创立', '1. New methods of teaching foreign languages are adopted in this institute. 该学院采用新的外语教学法。 2. Integrity and professionalism are the two main corporate values of the Institute. 诚信和专业精神是学会的两个主要机构价值观。 3. The UK\'s Securities & Investment Institute provides education and qualifications for many of these staff. 英国证券与投资协会为许多这样的员工提供培训和资格证书。 4. The police instituted an inquiry into the cause of the accident. 警方开始调查事故的原因。', '名词: instituter 过去式: instituted 过去分词: instituted 现在分词: instituting 第三人称单数: institutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conscience', '[\'kɑːnʃəns]', 'n.良心；是非之心；顾忌', '1. She was afflicted with conscience. 她受良心责备。 2. The thief\'s conscience smote him. 那个贼突然良心发现。 3. She gave him back the money she\'d stolen for the sake of her conscience. 为了不受良心的谴责，她把从他那偷来的钱还给他了。 4. This is a document that serves as the nation\'s conscience. 这是一份表明民族道德准则的文件。', '形容词: conscienceless');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imposing', '[ɪm\'poʊzɪŋ]', 'adj.令人难忘的；壮丽的 动词impose的现在分词.', '1. He was an imposing figure on stage. 他在舞台上的表演令人难忘。 2. The main hall of the temple is so imposing! 这个佛寺的大殿建造得真气派！ 3. She\'d never think of imposing herself. 她决不想勉强别人接纳自己。 4. You are always imposing on their generosity. 你总是在利用别人的慷慨而占便宜', '副词: imposingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chimpanzee', '[ˌtʃɪmpæn\'ziː]', 'n.黑猩猩', '1. Gorilla is bigger than chimpanzee. 大猩猩比黑猩猩大。 2. A South African zoo wants a chimpanzee to quit smoking cold turkey. 南非一家动物园要一只黑猩猩立即戒菸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exclaim', '[ɪk\'skleɪm]', 'v.大叫；呼喊；大声说出', '1. The children exclaimed with excitement. 孩子们兴奋地大叫。 2. \"How beautiful the lake is!\" we exclaimed. 我们叫喊着说,\"这个湖多美啊!\" 3. She exclaimed at the beautiful view. 她对这美丽的景色感到惊奇。 4. She exclaimed that she was innocent. 她大声呼喊她是无辜的。', '名词: exclaimer 过去式: exclaimed 过去分词: exclaimed 现在分词: exclaiming 第三人称单数: exclaims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('derive', '[dɪ\'raɪv]', 'v.获取；得自；起源', '1. We shall derive much benefit from reading good novels. 我们将从优秀小说中获得很大好处。 2. We derive our sustenance from the land. 我们从土地获取食物。 3. One kind of vacation is camping, from which many Americans derive pleasure and benefit. 露营是一种度假方式，许多美国人从中得到乐趣，受益匪浅。 4. If we start some a year earlier, we shall derive the benefits a year earlier. 我们如果早开始一年,我们可以早得利一年', '形容词: derivable 名词: deriver 过去式: derived 过去分词: derived 现在分词: deriving 第三人称单数: derives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('systematic', '[ˌsɪstə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.有系统的；分类的；体系的；有条理的', '1. He is making a systematic study of the subject. 他在对那一科目作系统的研究。 2. The school offered a systematic course in reading. 学校提供系统的阅读课程。 3. Science means systematic knowledge possessed as a result of practice and study. 科学是由于实践和研究的结果而获得的系统知识。 4. The systematic organization of the larger teams will result in better efficiency. 构建大组制体系有利于提高效率。', '副词: systematically 异体字: systematical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clump', '[klʌmp]', 'n.丛；块；沉重的声音 v.用沉重的脚步行走；丛生；使成簇', '1. Which month hospital receives brachial clump nerve best? 哪个月医院接臂丛神经最好了？ 2. It was as if he had hacked with his thick boots at a clump of bluebells. 仿佛他用自己的厚靴子无情地践踏了一丛野风信子。 3. The grain was rubbed out of the ears in the clump and scattered in the prepared soil. 将这块地上耳穗里的庄稼搓出并撒到备好的土地里。 4. I held a bit of the hearty earth in my hand to form a hard clump and added it to the bowl. 我用手捧起一点肥沃的土壤，并使其成为硬实的一整块，把它放进碗里。 5. Fast moving particles, however, cannot clump together on such small scales and, in fact, suppress the clumping of other matter. 可是快速移动的粒子不能以这种小比例范围丛生一起，事实抑制了其它物质丛生。', '形容词: clumpy 过去式: clumped 过去分词: clumped 现在分词: clumping 第三人称单数: clumps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('locate', '[\'loʊkeɪt]', 'vt.找出；把 ... 设置在；使坐落于 vi.住下来', '1. The general tried to locate the enemy\'s camp. 那位将军想找出敌人营地的位置。 2. They decided to locate a new school in the suburbs. 他们决定在郊区设置一所新学校。 3. The company wished to locate its new factory beside the river. 这家公司希望把新工厂建在河边。 4. After he retired, he went to locate in California. 他退休后在加里弗尼亚定居。', '形容词: locatable 名词: locater 过去式: located 过去分词: located 现在分词: locating 第三人称单数: locates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lettuce', '[\'letɪs]', 'n.莴苣；生菜；<俚>纸币', '1. She never grew lettuce in her garden. 她从不在她的花园里培育莴苣。 2. I like the delicious salad of crisp lettuce and tomatoes. 我喜欢这种脆莴苣和番茄做的沙拉,很好吃。 3. We need a head of lettuce, a bunch of carrots, and a bag of onions. 我们要一棵生菜，一把胡萝卜和一袋洋葱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shrink', '[ʃrɪŋk]', 'vi.收缩；退缩；萎缩；畏惧，害怕 vt.使收缩 n.收缩；萎缩 n.精神科医生', '1. Will this woolen sweater shrink when washed? 这件羊毛衫洗后会缩水吗？ 2. The company\'s profit margins shrank from 32.5% to 17%. 该公司的边际利润率从32.5%降到了17%。 3. We will never shrink from difficulties. 我们在困难面前决不退缩。 4. The economy is shrinking instead of growing. 经济正在萎缩而不是在增长中。 5. The hot water shrank my pullover. 我的套头毛衣遇热水后收缩了。 6. You can expect some shrink when the jeans are washed. 这种牛仔裤洗后要缩些水。 7. My aunt saw this shrink after her divorce. 我阿姨在离婚后去见过这位心理医生。', '形容词: shrinkable 名词: shrinker 过去式: shrank/shrunk 过去分词: shrunk/shrunken 现在分词: shrinking 第三人称单数: shrinks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assume', '[ə\'suːm]', 'vt.假定；设想；承担；(想当然的)认为；假装', '1. Let\'s assume it to be true. 让我们假定这是真的。 2. We assume his guilt. 我们假定他是有罪的。 3. They assumed their operational positions. 他们设想了自己在实施中的作用。 4. I am not afraid to assume the responsibility. 我不怕承担责任.', '形容词: assumable 副词: assumably 名词: assumer 过去式: assumed 过去分词: assumed 现在分词: assuming 第三人称单数: assumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hike', '[haɪk]', 'n.徒步旅行；远足；涨价 vi.远足；提高', '1. He always bring a canteen with him on a hike. 他作徒步旅行时总是带着水壶。 2. The storm upset their plans for a hike. 暴风雨破坏了他们的远足计划。 3. The government announced a 300 per cent hike in bread prices. 政府宣布面包涨价三倍。 4. He wants to hike round the world. 他打算徒步旅行环游世界一周。', '名词: hiker 过去式: hiked 过去分词: hiked 现在分词: hiking 第三人称单数: hikes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vascular', '[\'væskjələr]', 'adj.血管的；脉管的；充满活力的', '1. The basic disorder might be vascular dysfunction leading to local vasospasm and to systemic hypotension. 其基本的改变可能是血管的功能障碍导致局部的血管痉挛和低血压。 2. Furthermore, ECs obtained from these vascular malformations can be used as an experimental model to study SAH-induced vasoconstriction. 此外，这些来源于畸形血管的内皮细胞可作为研究蛛网膜下腔出血引发血管收缩的实验模型。', '名词: vascularity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('familiarize', '[fə\'mɪliəraɪz]', 'vt.使熟悉', '1. The first repetition drill serves to familiarize the students with the sounds in the dialogue. 第一部分的背诵练习是为了使学生熟悉一下对话的语调。 2. It is incumbent upon all users of this equipment to familiarize themselves with the safety procedure. 凡使用这种设备的人都应熟悉安全程序。', '名词: familiarization 过去式: familiarized 过去分词: familiarized 现在分词: familiarizing 第三人称单数: familiarizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repulsive', '[rɪ\'pʌlsɪv]', 'adj.令人厌恶的；排斥的', '1. Snakes are repulsive to some people. 蛇令一些人厌恶。 2. These exquisite creatures were positively repulsive. 这些精美的人物的确令人厌恶。 3. The interaction becomes repulsive. 相互作用成为排斥的了。 4. It is, depending on your point of view, a charming memento of the kissing session or a repulsive and embarrassing bruise. 这就靠你自己的观念来判断了，看这到底是一个充满诱惑的吻之纪念品，还是一个令人尴尬排斥的瘀伤。', '副词: repulsively 名词: repulsiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hemisphere', '[\'hemɪsfɪr]', 'n.半球', '1. the party out ofoffice 2. If you cut a round fruit into two, each half is a hemisphere. 如果你把一个圆的水果切成两半，每一半就是一个半球。 3. The Northern Hemisphere is the part of the world north of the equator, and the Southern Hemisphere is south of the equator. 北半球是地球赤道以北的部分，南半球是赤道以南的部分。', '形容词: hemispheric 副词: hemispherically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('permissive', '[pər\'mɪsɪv]', 'adj.放任的；纵容的；许可的；获准的', '1. Should parents be strict or permissive? 父母应该严格还是放任? 2. He claims that society has been far too permissive towards drug taking. 他认为社会对吸毒太纵容了。 3. First, democracy is basically a permissive system. 第一，民主，本质上，是一个许可体制。', '副词: permissively 名词: permissiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diction', '[\'dɪkʃn]', 'n.措辞；发音', '1. The diction of his answer is carefull. 他的回答措辞严谨。 2. The original was all her own, her own happy thoughts and gentle diction. 原稿由她一手拟定，出自她自己的高见和她自己的文雅措辞。 3. Clarity of diction is vital for a public speaker. 发音清晰对演说家至关重要。 4. Actors need training in diction. 演员需要训练发音。', '形容词: dictional 副词: dictionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('combat', '[\'kɑːmbæt]', 'n.战斗；试图解决 v.战斗；与 ... 斗争；试图解决 adj.战斗的', '1. The fighter planes quickly disengaged from the combat. 歼击机很快从战斗中撤出了。 2. He is stuck in the combat against this problem. 他在解决这个难题的过程中遇到了障碍。 3. The nation will combat all invaders. 这个民族将同所有的入侵者战斗。 4. The ship is combating the wind and waves. 那只船正与风浪搏斗。 5. The soldiers are ready to fly the 50 combat mission. 战士们已经准备好了执行第50号战斗任务。', '过去式: combated/combatted 过去分词: combated/combatted 现在分词: combating/combatting 第三人称单数: combats/combats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('radiate', '[\'reɪdieɪt]', 'v.放射；散发；辐射；流露', '1. Eight roads radiate from the square. 八条大道从广场呈辐射形伸展出去。 2. Heat radiated from the stove. 炉子散发的热量。 3. Heat radiates from the heating radiator and spreads to every corner of the room. 热从暖气片散发出来并传播到室内各个角落。 4. The radiance of electric lights radiates from the ceiling. 电灯的光芒从天花板上辐射下来。', '形容词: radiative 过去式: radiated 过去分词: radiated 现在分词: radiating 第三人称单数: radiates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drag', '[dræɡ]', 'v.拖；拉；迫使；缓慢行进；进行过久；扯进；打捞 n.拖；拉；累赘；阻力 n.男子穿的女子服装', '1. He dragged the heavy case across the floor. 他在地板上拖着那个沉重的箱子。 2. shrug aside 不予理会 3. She dragged herself out of bed, still half asleep. 她挣扎着起了床,还是睡眼惺忪。 4. She always drags behind us. 她总是在我们后面吃力地跟着。 5. The cat is really excited by the drag of the basket on the floor. 在地板上来来回回拖着篮子可着实让那只猫兴奋了一回。', '过去式: dragged 过去分词: dragged 现在分词: dragging 第三人称单数: drags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('personal', '[\'pɜːrsənl]', 'adj.私人的；个人的 n.(报刊)私人专栏', '1. I have something personal to discuss with you. 我有点私事和你商量。 2. I need your advice on a personal matter, but it\'s not about me. 有一件私事我想听听你的建议,但不是我的事。 3. It is my own, growing out of my personal concern. 是我自己提出的,完全出于我个人的关切。 4. Within two hours, I got my personal statement done. 仅花了两个小时,我就把个人陈述写好了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dessert', '[dɪ\'zɜːrt]', 'n.甜食，餐后甜点', '1. I like to have ice cream for dessert. 我喜欢在正餐后吃冰淇淋当甜点。 2. Can I have some fruit instead of the dessert? 可不可以不要甜点改要水果？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sick', '[sɪk]', 'adj.有病的；恶心的；腻烦的；晕的；令人毛骨悚然的 n.病人；呕吐物 vt.追逐；攻击；唆使', '1. He fell sick with malaria on a trip to Africa. 他在去非洲时患了疟疾。 2. He put a maid in to look after his sick wife. 他雇了1名女仆来照顾她的病妻。 3. You\'ll be sick if you eat any more of that candy. 如果你再吃那种糖果,就会感到恶心的。 4. I\'m sick of waiting around like this. 我讨厌透了像这样在一旁等著。 5. The sick need special care. 病人需要特别护理。 6. Sick\'em! 咬他们!', '比较级: sicker 最高级: sickest');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chary', '[\'tʃeri]', 'adj.谨慎的；节俭的', '1. A cat is chary of wetting its paws. 猫尽量避免弄湿它的脚掌。 2. They are chary of investing such an amount of money in the risky business. 他们对于在那项风险很大的生意中投资态度很谨慎。 3. He is chary of praise. 他吝于称赞别人。 4. Oh sure. The boss is very chary about taking on more people at the moment. 喔，那是当然，老板目前非常不轻易增聘人手。', '副词: charily 比较级: charier 最高级: chariest 名词: chariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defunct', '[dɪ\'fʌŋkt]', 'adj.死的；不能使用的；非现存的；失效的 n.死者', '1. A family name becomes defunct when the only heir dies without any son. 当唯一的继承人死去了之后没儿子，那这个姓就要绝迹了。 2. It is a defunct political organization. 这是一个解散了的政治组织。 3. Most of the time of the defunct had been passed in helping himself. 死者生前大部分时间都是用来造福自己。', '形容词: defunctive 名词: defunctness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('primitive', '[\'prɪmətɪv]', 'adj.原始的；简陋的 n.文艺复兴前的艺术家；原始人', '1. Primitive peoples deified the sun. 原始部落将太阳奉为神。 2. The constitution of a primitive society is not necessarily simple. 原始社会的结构并不一定就是简单的。 3. They built a primitive shelter out of the tree trunks 他们用一些树干建造了一个简陋的棚子。 4. Primitive people often lived in caves. 原始人常常住在山洞里。', '副词: primitively 名词: primitiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('independent', '[ˌɪndɪ\'pendənt]', 'adj.独立的；自主的；独自的；无偏见的 n.无党派者；独立派人士', '1. The former colonial possessions are now independent states. 以前的许多殖民地现已成为独立的国家。 2. You should learn to be independent of your parents. 你应该学习不要依赖父母。 3. Two independent investigators have reached virtually the same conclusions. 两个调查人员各自做出的结论简直完全一致。 4. He is an independent observer. 他是位无偏见的观察者。 5. The independent candidate is especially critical of the policy. 这位无党派候选人特别批评了该政策。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dignified', '[\'dɪɡnɪfaɪd]', 'adj.高贵的；威风的；有尊严的；气派的 动词dignify的过去式和过去分词', '1. People consider violet a dignified color. 人们认为紫色是高贵的颜色。 2. Her dignified bearing throughout the trial made everyone believe she was innocent. 在整个审讯的过程中，她那端庄的举止使得每个人都相信她是无辜的。 3. He turns into a dignified man. 他变得很有派头。 4. Captain Hoxworth was the most dignified and memorable man in Hawaii, and he knew it. 霍克斯沃思船长在夏威夷是最威风最有名的人。他自己也知道。', '副词: dignifiedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comedy', '[\'kɑːmədi]', 'n.喜剧；滑稽；幽默事件', '1. This comedy has had them rolling in the aisles for two weeks. 这出喜剧让观众们连续两个星期乐得前仰后合。 2. I prefer comedy to tragedy. 我喜欢喜剧而不喜欢悲剧。 3. The drama may be termed a comedy. 这部戏剧可称为喜剧。 4. Who could resist the comedy of American names? 谁能看到美国那些滑稽的地名而不发笑呢?', '名词复数: comedies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wield', '[wiːld]', 'v.行使；施加(影响)；使用(武器等)；挥舞', '1. People may wield the power in a democracy. 在民主国家里，人民可以行使权力。 2. She wields a lot of influence. 她是个很有影响力的人。 3. He decides to wield his pitiful weapon. 他决定动用他的可怜的武器了。 4. We must learn to wield the weapon of law effectively. 我们要学会使用和用好法律武器。', '形容词: wieldable 名词: wielder 过去式: wielded 过去分词: wielded 现在分词: wielding 第三人称单数: wields');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('match', '[mætʃ]', 'n.对手；火柴；比赛；配偶；般配的人 v.相配；和...相配；相一致；较量', '1. He was very good at tennis, but he met his match when he played McEnroe. 他的网球打得很好，但当他与麦肯罗对打时，他遇到对手了。 2. I am no match for her when it comes to language. 在语言能力方面我根本不是她的对手。 3. The smoker tossed away the lighted match and so caused a fire. 那个抽烟的人随手扔掉火柴棒，引起了一场火灾。 4. A high standard of play marked the match between the two teams. 这两个队的比赛表现了很高的技术水平。 5. Will you match me this cloth? 你可以帮我搭配一下这块布料吗?', '名词: matcher 过去式: matched 过去分词: matched 现在分词: matching 第三人称单数: matches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slug', '[slʌɡ]', 'n.蛞蝓；鼻涕虫；动作缓慢的人 n.子弹；铅字条；[物]斯勒格（质量单位） n.重击 v.加铅字条于；用力打', '1. The small garden slug can stretch its body to enter worm holes. 渺小的庭院蛞蝓能把身体伸长而钻进虫子洞里。 2. I raised a fist to slug Eddie. 我举拳重击埃迪。', '过去式: slugged 过去分词: slugged 现在分词: slugging 第三人称单数: slugs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proximity', '[prɑːk\'sɪməti]', 'n.接近；亲近', '1. Their house is in close proximity to ours. 他们的房子很接近我们的。 2. The sum is in close proximity to the amount of revenue. 总数接近岁入之值。 3. My proximity to your office adds flexibility. 我住的地方靠近贵公司，工作可以说是更加方便有利。 4. Marriages in proximity of blood are forbidden by the law. 法律规定禁止近亲结婚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('awareness', '[ə\'wernəs]', 'n.认识；觉察；意识', '1. There is a general awareness that smoking is harmful. 人们普遍认识到吸烟有害健康。 2. This incident has sharpened public awareness of the economic crisis. 这件事提高了公众对经济危机的认识。 3. Youth glided past without our awareness. 青春在我们不知不觉中逝去。 4. He has good awareness to fashion industry. 他有对时尚行业敏感的嗅觉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('choke', '[tʃoʊk]', 'vi.窒息；阻塞；说不出话 vt.使窒息；阻塞；抑制；使说不出话 n.窒息；阻塞；阻风门', '1. She looked like she was going to choke. 她看起来仿佛都要窒息了。 2. She found it hard to choke down her anger. 她感到难以压下心中的怒火。 3. She choked with emotion. 她激动得说不出话来。 4. Very small toys can choke a baby. 很小的玩具可使婴儿窒息。 5. Very small toys can choke a baby. 很小的玩具可使婴儿窒息。', '过去式: choked 过去分词: choked 现在分词: choking 第三人称单数: chokes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rhinoceros', '[raɪ\'nɑːsərəs]', 'n.犀牛；(对受攻击、批评、侮辱等)麻木不仁', '1. The rhinoceros has one horn on its nose. 犀牛鼻子上有一个角。 2. The game wardens tranquillized the rhinoceros with a drugged dart. 猎物保护区管理员用麻醉射器让犀牛静了下来。 3. Say what you like about him, he won\'t care; he\'s got a skin like a rhinoceros. 你想说他什么就直说好了，他不会在乎的。他呀，脸皮厚得跟犀牛皮一样。', '名词复数: rhinoceros');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sweep', '[swiːp]', 'v.打扫；掠过；扫视；席卷；全胜；清除 n.清扫；连绵一片；席卷；掠过；范围；搜寻；(竞赛中)全胜；赌金', '1. He picked up the broom to help me sweep the floor. 他拿起扫帚帮我扫地。 2. They asked the little boy to sweep the room clean. 他们叫那个小男孩把房间打扫干净。 3. His fingers swept the keys of the piano. 他的手指在钢琴键盘上轻快地移动。 4. The breeze sweeps the crystal mirror of the pool. 微风掠过清如明鉴的一泓池水。 5. This floor needs a good sweep. 这地板需要好好清扫一下。', '名词: sweeper 过去式: swept 过去分词: swept 现在分词: sweeping 第三人称单数: sweeps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ravage', '[\'rævɪdʒ]', 'v.毁坏；破坏；掠夺 n.破坏；蹂躏', '1. The forests were ravaged by fire. 森林毁于火灾。 2. Is it for you to ravage seas and land? 你认为海洋和陆地将被破坏吗？ 3. Bands of soldiers ravaged the village. 成群的士兵洗劫了村庄。 4. The rape of the countryside had a profound ravage on them. 对乡村的掠夺给他们造成严重创伤。', '名词: ravager 过去式: ravaged 过去分词: ravaged 现在分词: ravaging 第三人称单数: ravages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grazing', '[\'ɡreɪzɪŋ]', 'n.放牧；牧场 动词graze的现在分词.', '1. We will talk more about rotational grazing next week. 下周,我们将谈论更多有关循环放牧的内容。 2. They made only 40 per cent of their income from grazing. 他们的收入只有百分之四十来自放牧。 3. Experts say rotational grazing like this is extremely important for marginal land. 专家指出，像这样循环放牧对边缘土地极其重要。 4. Small family groups must make the most of the rich grazing before the summer ends. 小牧民家庭必须赶在夏季结束前尽量在牧草富足的地方放牧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impale', '[ɪm\'peɪl]', 'v.刺穿；钉住；使陷入困境', '1. In former times, prisoners\' heads were impaled on pointed stakes. 从前的人把监犯的头钉在尖桩上。', '异体字: empale 名词: impalement 过去式: impaled 过去分词: impaled 现在分词: impaling 第三人称单数: impales');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vaccine', '[væk\'siːn]', 'n.疫苗', '1. The vaccine was used to protect the whole population against infection. 这种疫苗用以为全体居民预防传染病。 2. The smallpox vaccine has saved many lives. 天花疫苗挽救了许多人的生命。 3. The search for a new vaccine took priority over all other medical research. 在各种医药研究中，应首先解决寻找新疫苗的问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('denounce', '[dɪ\'naʊns]', 'v.谴责；告发；通告废除', '1. The minister\'s action was denounced in the newspaper. 部长的行为受到报界的指责。 2. American trade policies have been denounced by some European governments. 一些欧洲政府指责美国的贸易政策。 3. They denounced him to the police as a criminal. 他们向警方告发他是罪犯。 4. Somebody denounced him to the military police as a spy. 有人向宪兵队告发他为间谍。', '名词: denouncement 过去式: denounced 过去分词: denounced 现在分词: denouncing 第三人称单数: denounces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crucial', '[\'kruːʃl]', 'adj.决定性的；关键的', '1. Her work has been crucial to the project\'s success. 她的工作对项目的成功至关重要。 2. It is crucial that we get this right. 我们把这个问题弄明白是极其重要的。 3. Trust is crucial for successful friendship. 相互信任是维系友谊的关键。 4. The battle had reached a crucial stage. 战斗已到了关键阶段。', '副词: crucially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tragedy', '[\'trædʒədi]', 'n.悲剧；灾难；惨事', '1. Tragedy is in store for that poor girl from the beginning. 从一开始，那个女孩的悲剧就是不可避免的。 2. Shakespeare\'s Hamlet is a very famous tragedy. 莎士比亚的《哈姆雷特》是一部十分著名的悲剧。 3. It was not long before tragedy struck again. 没多久，灾难又再次降临。 4. This recent tragedy has put the manufacturersof the drug squarely in the dock. 新近发生的这一悲惨事件使药品厂商受到指控。', '名词复数: tragedies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advocate', '[\'ædvəkeɪt]', 'v.提倡；主张 n.拥护者；提倡者；律师；辩护者', '1. Many educators advocate a liberal education. 很多教育家提倡通才教育。 2. We don\'t advocate learning by rote. 死记硬背的学习方法，我们是不提倡的。 3. Many people advocate building more hospitals. 许多人主张增设医院。 4. We advocate higher salaries for teachers. 我们主张涨老师的工资。 5. She is a passionate advocate of education reform. 她是一名教育改革的热情拥护者。', '形容词: advocatory 名词: advocator 过去式: advocated 过去分词: advocated 现在分词: advocating 第三人称单数: advocates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('volume', '[\'vɑːljuːm]', 'n.卷；体积；册；音量；容量', '1. This volume contains selections from his early works. 该卷包含了他的早期作品文选。 2. This volume is foxed on the flyleaf. 这卷书的空白页发黄了。 3. A gas has neither definite volume nor definite shape. 气体既无一定体积,又无一定形状。 4. Is that volume still in print? 那册书还能买到吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flavoring', '[\'fleɪvrɪŋ]', 'n.调味料 动词flavor的现在分词形式. =flavouring.', '1. But Eastern cooks have been using glutamate-rich seaweed as flavoring for more than 1000 years. 但一千多年来，东方的厨师一直用富含谷氨酸盐的海藻当调味料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('healthful', '[\'helθfl]', 'adj.有益健康的；使人健康的；卫生的', '1. Plenty of sleep is healthful. 充足的睡眠有益于健康。 2. I hope you will recover soon under this healthful climate. 我希望在这种有益健康的气候下，你会很快地康复起来。', '副词: healthfully 名词: healthfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emulate', '[\'emjuleɪt]', 'vt.效法；尽力赶上 [计算机] 仿真.', '1. You should emulate his good example. 你应该效法他的好榜样。 2. The proverb tells us to emulate the industry of the ant. 这格言告诉我们要效法蚂蚁的勤勉。 3. I wish he\'d stop holding the elder brother as an example to emulate. 我希望他不再把哥哥作为自己的学习榜样。 4. You must work hard to emulate your sister. 你必须努力工作, 赶上你姐姐。 5. If one computer system or program emulates another, it behaves in the same way. 如果一台计算机系统或者程序模拟另外一台电脑,它表现在以同样的方式运行。', '形容词: emulative 副词: emulatively 名词: emulator 过去式: emulated 过去分词: emulated 现在分词: emulating 第三人称单数: emulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mere', '[mɪr]', 'adj.仅仅的；纯粹的', '1. Don\'t scold him, he is a mere child. 别责备他,他只不过是个孩子。 2. Her liberal views were soon revealed as mere posturing. 她那些开明的观点很快地就暴露出只不过是做做样子而已。 3. The peasant laboured for a mere pittance. 农民仅仅是为了微不足道的收入而辛苦地劳作。 4. A mere child cannot do the work of a man. 仅仅是个孩子是不能做成人工作的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pave', '[peɪv]', 'vt.铺路；铺设；铺满；安排', '1. The road was paved with cobblestones. 那条路是用鹅卵石铺成的。 2. The town council decided to pave the square before the Hall. 市议会决定在市政厅前铺一个广 3. The bricks are to pave the courtyard. 这些砖要用来铺院子。 4. Our garden is well paved with flowers. 我们的园子里鲜花遍地。', '名词: paver 过去式: paved 过去分词: paved 现在分词: paving 第三人称单数: paves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('optical', '[\'ɑːptɪkl]', 'adj.视觉的；光学的', '1. The optical system of the eye stimulate cell of the retina. 眼睛的视觉系统刺激视网膜内的细胞。 2. A mirage is an optical illusion. 海市蜃楼是一种视错觉。 3. The canal on Mars is believed to be an optical illusion. 火星运河被认为是一种视觉错觉。 4. Microscopes and telescopes are optical instruments. 望远镜和显微镜是光学仪器。', '副词: optically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disband', '[dɪs\'bænd]', 'v.解散；遣散', '1. The school was disbanded at noon. 学校在中午被解散了。 2. The army was disbanded when the war came to an end. 战争结束时，军队即被解散。 3. The government tried to disband the illegal organization. 政府企图解散那个非法组织。', '名词: disbandment 过去式: disbanded 过去分词: disbanded 现在分词: disbanding 第三人称单数: disbands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instrument', '[\'ɪnstrəmənt]', 'n.仪器；乐器；工具；器械 v.用器械（或仪器）装备；向…提交文书', '1. This instrument monitors the patient\'s heartbeats. 这台仪器监听病人的心跳。 2. He can play nearly every musical instrument. 他几乎能演奏每一件乐器。 3. A plough is an instrument used for farming. 犁是用于耕作的工具。 4. The hospital imported some surgical instruments. 医院进口了一些外科器械。', '过去式: instrumented 过去分词: instrumented 现在分词: instrumenting 第三人称单数: instruments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('desolate', '[\'desələt]', 'adj.荒凉的；荒芜的；孤单寂寞的', '1. We saw few houses in the desolate valley. 在这荒凉的山谷里,我们很少见到房子。 2. The railway station became desolate in the war. 战争期间，这个火车站变得荒凉了。 3. Heavy rain will wash away the soil from desolate hills. 大雨将把泥土从荒凉的山丘上冲走。 4. This place is desolate of all vegetation. 这个地方不长草木。', '副词: desolately 名词: desolateness 过去式: desolated 过去分词: desolated 现在分词: desolating 第三人称单数: desolates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opulence', '[\'ɒpjələns]', 'n.富裕；丰富', '1. He owes his opulence to work hard. 他的财富乃辛勤工作得来。 2. His eyes had never beheld such opulence. 他从未见过这样的财富。 3. The room was decorated with stagy opulence. 那房间装饰得富丽堂皇，像戏台似的。', '异体字: opulency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squirrel', '[\'skwɜːrəl]', 'n.松鼠；松鼠皮毛 vt.储存', '1. The squirrel is a lovely small animal. 松鼠是一种可爱的小动物。 2. The squirrel ran up a tree and got out of my reach. 松鼠跑到树上去了，我逮不着。 3. The squirrel hoards up nuts for the winter. 松鼠储藏坚果以防冬天。 4. Nervous householders continue to squirrel more money away in the banks. 不安的居民持续不断地把更多钱存入银行里。', '过去式: squirreled/squirrelled 过去分词: squirreled/squirrelled 现在分词: squirreling/squirrelling 第三人称单数: squirrels/squirrels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excuse', '[ɪk\'skjuːs]', 'vt.原谅；辩解 n.理由；辩解；借口', '1. Excuse me, but I must say you are completely wrong. 对不起，但是我必须说你完全错了。 2. I hope you will excuse me if I have to leave early. 如果我必须早些离开,希望你能原谅我。 3. He told a real whopper to excuse his lateness. 他撒了个大谎为自己的迟到辩解。 4. His excuse for being late was that he had missed the train. 他迟到的理由是没有赶上火车。', '形容词: excusable 副词: excusably 名词: excusableness 过去式: excused 过去分词: excused 现在分词: excusing 第三人称单数: excuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('still', '[stɪl]', 'adj.静止的；不动的；静寂的 adv.更；仍然；静止地 v.使...平静下来 n.蒸馏器；寂静；定格照', '1. Beware of silent dog and still water. 提防不吠的犬,小心静止的水。 2. The room was still at the end of the speech. 演讲结束的时候，房间里寂静无声。 3. Although she felt ill, she still went to work. 她虽然觉得身体不舒服，但仍然去上班了。 4. Although he is eighty,he is still very much alive. 他虽有八十岁了,但仍然充满了活力。 5. The food stilled the baby\'s cries. 食物使婴儿停止了哭泣。', '比较级: stiller 最高级: stillest 过去式: stilled 过去分词: stilled 现在分词: stilling 第三人称单数: stills');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('broaden', '[\'brɔːdn]', 'v.变宽；扩大；开阔', '1. The workmen dug down the wall in order to broaden the road. 工人们掘倒了那堵墙，以便扩宽路面。 2. You can not determine the length of your life, however, you can broaden it. 你无法决定人生的长度,但是你却可以让它变得更加宽广。 3. By reading, we can broaden our horizon. 通过阅读，我们可以扩大视野。 4. It is our company\'s aim to broaden the range of services continually. 不断地扩大服务领域，是本公司的目标。', '名词: broadener 过去式: broadened 过去分词: broadened 现在分词: broadening 第三人称单数: broadens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('locomotion', '[ˌloʊkə\'moʊʃn]', 'n.运动；移动；转位', '1. By land, air or sea, birds are masters of locomotion. 无论是通过陆地,飞越空中还是穿过海洋,鸟应算是运动能手了。 2. The simplest behavior of a robot is locomotion. 机器人最简单的行为是移动。 3. Food sources also elicit oriented locomotion and recognition behavior patterns in most insects. 食物源也引诱大多数昆虫定向迁移和识别行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disgrace', '[dɪs\'ɡreɪs]', 'n.耻辱 v.耻辱；丢脸', '1. The dirty classrooms are a disgrace to the school. 肮脏的教室是学校的耻辱。 2. Her actions brought disgrace on his family. 她的行为给她的家庭带来了耻辱。 3. You will bring disgrace on yourself by doing this. 你这样做会给自己带来耻辱。 4. He quit in disgrace over the bribe. 他因受贿而不光彩地辞职了。 5. He will die before he shall disgrace himself. 他宁肯死而决不受侮辱。', '名词: disgracer 过去式: disgraced 过去分词: disgraced 现在分词: disgracing 第三人称单数: disgraces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insect', '[\'ɪnsekt]', 'n.昆虫；虫子；卑微的人', '1. The insect bit him and drew blood from his arm. 那只昆虫叮在他的手臂上吸血。 2. A cocoon is a kind of silk covering made by an insect. 蚕茧是由昆虫制造的一种由丝组成的外包层。 3. She stamped on the insect and killed it. 她踩死了一只虫子。 4. A locust is a kind of destructive insect. 蝗虫是一种害虫。', '形容词: insectival 名词复数: insects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comprise', '[kəm\'praɪz]', 'vt.构成；包含', '1. This month\'s figures are comprised in the total. 这个月的数字已包含在总数之内。 2. Fifteen separate republics comprised the Soviet Union. 苏联由十五个加盟共和国组成。 3. Fifty states comprise the Union. 五十个州组成美国。 4. Twelve departments comprise this university. 12个系组成了这所大学。', '形容词: comprisable 过去式: comprised 过去分词: comprised 现在分词: comprising 第三人称单数: comprises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forage', '[\'fɔːrɪdʒ]', 'n.粮草；饲料；搜寻粮草 v.喂；掠夺', '1. She teaches them to fish, forage, hunt, and defend themselves. 她教他们捕鱼，搜寻粮草，追捕，和防卫它们自己。 2. Flickers are woodpeckers that can hammer trees but prefer to forage on the ground. 闪烁啄木鸟能敲打树木但更喜欢到地面搜寻粮草。 3. There is much forage for the cattle. 那儿有很多喂牛的饲料。 4. Most species provide good forage. 大多数种提供好饲料。 5. There is much forage for the cattle. 那儿有很多喂牛的饲料。', '名词: forager 过去式: foraged 过去分词: foraged 现在分词: foraging 第三人称单数: forages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('capacious', '[kə\'peɪʃəs]', 'adj.容量大的；广阔的；宽敞的', '1. He has a capacious memory. 他有丰富的记忆力。 2. It is also equipped with capacious dustbin. 它还配有大容量的垃圾箱。 3. People is chickenshit, heart is capacious. 人是渺小的，心灵是广阔的。 4. Gradually his capacious chin encroached upon the borders of the white cravat. 他的广阔的下巴逐渐侵占了白领带的边界。', '副词: capaciously 名词: capaciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('controversial', '[ˌkɑːntrə\'vɜːrʃl]', 'adj.有争议的；引起争论的', '1. We tried to stay away from controversial topics at the dinner party. 晚宴上我们尽力避免一些有争议的话题。 2. This is a controversial question. 这是个引起争论的问题。', '副词: controversially 名词: controversialist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subway', '[\'sʌbweɪ]', 'n.地铁；地下通道', '1. She saw us on the subway. 在地铁站她见到我们了 2. I want to get there by subway. 我想乘地铁去那儿。 3. Last Sunday, a News pressman named Gerald Boyd got worked over with baseball bats on his way to the subway and no one except us gave it much attention. 上星期日，纽约每日新闻一个名字叫波伊德的印刷工人在去地铁途中被人用球棒痛殴。除我们以外没人注意。 4. Use the subway to cross the road. 请走地下通道穿越马路。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('virtue', '[\'vɜːrtʃuː]', 'n.美德；德行；优点；贞操', '1. Fidelity to engagement is a virtue. 信守诺言是一种美德。 2. My neighbor is a man of highest virtue. 我的邻居是一个具有高尚品德的人。 3. He said his plan had the virtue of being the easiest to implement. 他说他的计划的优点是最简单易行。 4. Meekness is a virtue he appreciates in his wife. 温顺是他所欣赏的妻子的优点之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('counterpart', '[\'kaʊntərpɑːrt]', 'n.职务相当的人；对应物；相似之物；副本', '1. The secretary of state is the counterpart of the foreign minister. 国务卿相当于外交部长。 2. The sale director phoned her counterpart in the other firm. 这位销售主任给另一家公司的销售主任打电话。 3. Night is the counterpart of day. 黑夜与白天相辅相成。 4. I racked my memory in vain for its counterpart in literature: perhaps you could think of one. 我绞尽脑汁也想不出它在文学中的对等物，也许你可以想出一个。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defiant', '[dɪ\'faɪənt]', 'adj.挑衅的；目中无人', '1. He put his paw on the prize and glared across the water with a defiant growl. 他把他的爪子放在猎获物上，盯着河对岸，发出一声挑衅的吼叫。 2. Correspondents say the appointment seems intended to send a defiant message to South Korea. 通讯员称该任命似乎意在向韩国发出挑衅的信号。 3. What he said showed he was really defiant. 他所说的话显示出他真是目中无人。 4. Bellatrix remained defiant to the end. 直到审判的最后，贝拉特里克斯仍保持着她的桀骜不驯，目中无人。', '副词: defiantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concerned', '[kən\'sɜːrnd]', 'adj.担忧的；关心的；关切的；有关的', '1. Please don\'t be concerned about me. 请不要为我担心。 2. Concerned parents held a meeting. 忧心忡忡的家长们开了一次会。 3. We are all concerned about his health. 我们都非常关心他的健康。 4. There is a concerned look on his face. 他脸上露出关切的表情。', '名词: concern');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pancreas', '[\'pæŋkriəs]', 'n.胰脏', '1. I didn\'t even know what a pancreas was. 我当时甚至不知道胰脏究竟是什么。 2. Metastasis of renal cell carcinoma to the pancreas is uncommon. 摘要肾细胞癌很少转移到胰脏。', '形容词: pancreatic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disunite', '[ˌdɪsju\'naɪt]', 'vt.使分离；使不和', '1. To separate(people or groups,for example;disunite. 把(如人群或组)分开;使不团结 2. To part or divide; disunite; disconnect. 离；分；分开；分离。 3. To separate(people or groups, for example); disunite. 把（如人群或组）分开；使不团结 4. to disunite the links of a chain 拆开一条铁链的链环', '过去式: disunited 过去分词: disunited 现在分词: disuniting 第三人称单数: disunites');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cozy', '[\'koʊzi]', 'adj.舒适的；惬意的 v.靠近；取悦 n.保温罩 =cosy(英).', '1. He lives in a cozy little room. 他住在一个舒适的小屋里。 2. I felt all cozy tucked up in bed. 我钻进被窝里，暖暖和和舒服极了。 3. That night was so peaceful and cozy. 是夜如此平静惬意。 4. In the morning we found all the children cozied up together in the same bed. 早晨，所有的小孩都挤到了一张床上。 5. I made a super cute tea cosy out of a recycled wool blanket. 我用旧毯子上拆下来的线做了一个非常可爱的茶具保温罩。', '副词: cozily 名词: coziness 名词复数: cozies 过去式: cozied/cosied 过去分词: cozied/cosied 现在分词: cozying/cosying 第三人称单数: cozies/cosies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flavor', '[\'fleɪvə]', 'n.风味；特殊的滋味；风格；调味品 vt.加调料于...；给...添加情趣', '1. The course has a distinctive Italian flavor. 这道菜很有意大利餐的风味。 2. I don\'t like the flavor of onion. 我不喜欢洋葱的味道。 3. These works have a strong flavor of rural life. 这些作品散发着浓郁的乡土气息。 4. She flavored the fish with sugar and vinegar. 她用糖和醋给鱼调味。', '形容词: flavorless 名词: flavorer 过去式: flavored 过去分词: flavored 现在分词: flavoring 第三人称单数: flavors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suppose', '[sə\'poʊz]', 'vt.假设；假定；认为；想；应该；让(虚拟语气) vi.推测', '1. Suppose you have a thousand dollars, what will you do with it. 假设你有一千美元，你会用它做什么。 2. Let us suppose another planet with conditions similar to those on the earth. 让我们假定另外有一个具有和地球上相似条件的行星。 3. Some religions suppose that there is a Heaven physically above the earth. 一些宗教认为地球上面真有一个天国。 4. I suppose we shall be having some sort of celebration for the bride. 我想我们还是来为新娘庆贺一番吧。 5. I suppose he would be about fifty when he obtained a doctorate. 我推测他获得博士学位时大概是五十岁左右。', '过去式: supposed 过去分词: supposed 现在分词: supposing 第三人称单数: supposes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aspect', '[\'æspekt]', 'n.方面；方位；外观；外貌', '1. This is only one aspect of the problem. 这只是问题的一个方面。 2. He has made progress in every aspect. 他在各方面都有起色。 3. The building has a southern aspect. 那座建筑是朝南的。 4. The open spaces differ according to aspect. 开敞空地随方位而不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intimidate', '[ɪn\'tɪmɪdeɪt]', 'vt.胁迫；威胁；恐吓', '1. Nobody was going to intimidate them. 没有人能胁迫他们。 2. He was intimidated into silence. 他吓得不敢作声。 3. Bob intimidate the witness into silence. 鲍勃威胁证人保持沉默。 4. Your sons don\'t intimidate me. And neither do you. 你的儿子们威胁不了我,你也一样。', '副词: intimidatingly 名词: intimidation 过去式: intimidated 过去分词: intimidated 现在分词: intimidating 第三人称单数: intimidates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consequence', '[\'kɑːnsəkwens]', 'n.结果；后果；重要性；影响', '1. It terrified me to contemplate the consequence of your action. 一想到你行动的后果,我就感到害怕。 2. He studied hard, and in consequence he passed the exam. 他努力学习，因此通过了考试。 3. Happiness is not a reward it is a consequence. 幸福不是报偿，而是结果。 4. In consequence of his bad conduct he was dismissed. 由于行为不良，他被开除了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('antiquity', '[æn\'tɪkwəti]', 'n.古代；古物；古迹', '1. The culture of antiquity was rediscovered. 古代文化重见天日。 2. Animals and plants of remote antiquity turned to fossils. 远古的动植物变成了化石。 3. There are many legends about the heroes of antiquity. 有许多关于古代英雄的传说。 4. The Roman legion was the ultimate military formation of antiquity. 罗马的军团是古代异常强大的军事作战团队。', '名词复数: antiquities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delight', '[dɪ\'laɪt]', 'n.高兴；快乐 v.(使)高兴；(使)欣喜', '1. She clapped her hands in delight. 她高兴地拍手。 2. The children were prancing about with delight. 孩子们高兴得蹦蹦跳跳。 3. He takes great delight in painting. 他爱好绘画。 4. We delight in going for long walks in the country. 我们乐于去乡间远足。', '过去式: delighted 过去分词: delighted 现在分词: delighting 第三人称单数: delights 形容词: delightful 副词: delightfully');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wholesome', '[\'hoʊlsəm]', 'adj.有益健康的；合乎卫生的', '1. Bread and milk is wholesome breakfast. 面包和牛奶加有益于健康的早餐。 2. You should read some wholesome books. 你应当读些有益的书。 3. It is not wholesome to eat without washing your hands. 不洗手吃饭是不卫生的。', '副词: wholesomely 比较级: wholesomer 最高级: wholesomest 名词: wholesomeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spice', '[spaɪs]', 'n.调味品；香料；情趣 v.用香料调味；给…增添趣味', '1. The cook disguised the flavour with spice. 厨师巧用调料，使人们尝不出食品的原味。 2. Variety is the spice of life. 变化是生活的调味品。 3. Please add more spices to the cake. 请给蛋糕多加点香料。 4. Saffron is an extremely expensive spice. 番红花是一种非常昂贵的香料。 5. Have you spiced this cake? 这蛋糕中加香料了吗？', '过去式: spiced 过去分词: spiced 现在分词: spicing 第三人称单数: spices');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('internship', '[\'ɪntɜːrnʃɪp]', 'n.实习生职位；实习期', '1. He recently finished a six-month internship at Puma footwear. 他最近完成了一项为期6个月的实习在美洲豹鞋类. 2. I have served one-year internship at local news agency. 我在当地的新闻社实习过一年。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deceptive', '[dɪ\'septɪv]', 'adj.骗人的；虚伪的；诈欺的', '1. Appearances are often deceptive. 外表常常会骗人的。 2. There is nothing so clear and nothing more deceptive than emotions. 再也没有像情感那么清楚也没有比情感更容易骗人的了。 3. Deceptive advertising has damaged the company\'s image among the consumer. 虚假广告已损坏了该公司在消费者中的形象。', '名词: deceptiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('butter', '[\'bʌtər]', 'n.黄油；奶油 vt.涂黄油；奉承', '1. inflict symbolically 2. My mother asked me to cream the butter and sugar together. 妈妈让我把黄油和糖搅成奶油状。 3. She cooks omelets in butter as they do in France. 她用奶油做法国式的蛋卷。 4. She filmed a slice of bread with butter. 她涂一层薄薄的奶油在一片面包上。 5. I\'ll butter the bread. 我会给面包涂上黄油。', '过去式: buttered 过去分词: buttered 现在分词: buttering 第三人称单数: butters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affirm', '[ə\'fɜːrm]', 'vt.证实；断言；肯定', '1. Scientists cannot affirm the existence of life on other planets. 科学家们还不能证实在其它星球上有生命存在。 2. I affirm that what he said is true. 我断言他所说的是实情。 3. They affirmed that the girl did quite a bit of reading. 他们断言这个女孩子读了不少书。 4. I can affirm that no one will lose their job. 我可以肯定，谁都不会丢掉工作。', '形容词: affirmable 副词: affirmably 名词: affirmer 过去式: affirmed 过去分词: affirmed 现在分词: affirming 第三人称单数: affirms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('morbid', '[\'mɔːrbɪd]', 'adj.病态的；不正常的', '1. She always has a morbid imagination. 她总在做病态的想像。 2. Why do you like going to cemeteries so much? Is it some kind of morbid curiosity? 你为什么这么爱去墓地？是不是有些不太正常？', '副词: morbidly 名词: morbidness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trivial', '[\'trɪviəl]', 'adj.不重要的；琐碎的', '1. It\'s a trivial matter and not worth fighting about. 区区小事不值得争吵。 2. He could remember every trivial incident in great detail. 他能把每件小事的细节都记得很清楚。 3. I object to being jumped upon for trivial matter like this. 我讨厌因这种小事而受人责备。 4. Don\'t be angry over such trivial matters. 别为这些琐事生气。', '副词: trivially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lunar', '[\'luːnər]', 'adj.月亮的；阴历的；银的', '1. The astronauts piloted their craft down to the lunar surface. 宇航员驾驶宇宙飞船在月球表面降落。 2. Lunar eclipse occur when the earth\'s shadow fall on the moon. 地球的影子落在月球上时,就发生月蚀。 3. It was reported that there would be a lunar eclipse tomorrow evening. 据报道说，明天晚上有月食。 4. All traditional Chinese festivals are lunar calendar festivals. 中国的传统节日都是按照太阴历计算的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fateful', '[\'feɪtfl]', 'adj.宿命的；重大的；决定性的', '1. I relive that fateful day over and over in my mind. 我在脑海里不断地重温那决定命运的日子。 2. How can you overlook these fateful events? 你怎么能忽略了这些重大的事件? 3. This step involved many fateful consequences. 这一步骤带来了许多严重的后果。 4. The coming months will be fraught with fateful decisions. 未来数月将充满重大的决定。', '副词: fatefully 名词: fatefulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sear', '[sɪr]', 'vt.使 ... 干枯；烤焦；用强烈的感情影响 vi.变得干枯 adj.枯萎的；烤焦的 n.烤焦的痕迹', '1. The cold wind seared all the flowers. 冷风使所有的花都枯萎了。 2. A cloth was seared by the heat of the oven. 一块布被烤箱烧焦了。 3. The novel is a searing indictment of urban poverty. 这部小说是对城市贫困的震撼心灵的控诉。 4. The terrible experience is seared into my memory. 那次可怕的经历铭刻在我的记忆中。 5. The autumn breeze blows down sear leaves. 秋风吹落枯萎的树叶。 6. That sear face has a Japanese name, from the old time of Japan, it had already play the piano in the old music classroom. 那张烤焦的脸有个日本名字，从日据时代就开始在老旧的教室里弹琴。', '过去式: seared 过去分词: seared 现在分词: searing 第三人称单数: sears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('filter', '[\'fɪltər]', 'n.过滤器；滤色镜；滤光器 v.过滤；渗透', '1. We usually clear the water with a filter. 我们通常用过滤器使水净化。 2. You can also filter to focus on specific areas. 你也可以设置过滤器来只关注一些特定的区域。 3. Filter selection is made using inherent spectra. 滤色镜的选择必须利用固有光谱。 4. A yellow filter is placed in front of the camera lens to assure that no blue light will be imaged. 为了不使蓝光进入相机而成像，可在相机的透镜前加一黄滤色镜。 5. It won\'t take long to filter the coffee. 用不了多少时间就可以把咖啡过滤好。', '形容词: filterless 名词: filterer 过去式: filtered 过去分词: filtered 现在分词: filtering 第三人称单数: filters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genteel', '[dʒen\'tiːl]', 'adj.文雅的；有教养的', '1. She is too genteel for words. 她说话太咬文嚼字了。 2. You are genteel enough, you look like a lady. 你是够文雅的，看上去象个大家闺秀。 3. He came from a genteel family. 他出身於有教养的家庭。', '副词: genteelly 名词: genteelness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('identical', '[aɪ\'dentɪkl]', 'adj.同一的；相同的', '1. This is the identical hotel we stayed at last year. 这就是我们去年住过的旅馆。 2. Your appearance is identical to hers. 你的相貌和她的一模一样。 3. They\'re wearing identical clothes. 他们穿着完全相同的衣服。', '副词: identically 名词: identicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('auditorium', '[ˌɔːdɪ\'tɔːriəm]', 'n.礼堂；观众席', '1. The auditorium seats 3,000 people. 这个礼堂可坐三千人。 2. The stage is thrust forward into the auditorium. 舞台向前突出，伸入观众席。 3. The competition hasn\'t begun, but you can already hear the hubbub from the auditorium. 比赛还没开始，观众席上已经人声鼎沸了。', '名词复数: auditoriums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extraneous', '[ɪk\'streɪniəs]', 'adj.外来的；无关的', '1. Reductant from an extraneous source is introduced. 外来的还原剂被引进来。 2. Because of the extraneous and uncontrolled factors, those may affect the dependent variable. 由于许多外来的无法控制的因素，这些因素可能影响应变因素。 3. The only extraneous item I may carry is a gift. 我带的唯一与旅行无关的物件是礼物。 4. Extraneous null statements are not always harmless. 无关的空语句并非总是无害的。', '副词: extraneously 名词: extraneousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('retreat', '[rɪ\'triːt]', 'n.撤退；改变；隐居处 v.撤退；改变；退避；缩回象棋的棋子', '1. The troop made good their retreat from the occupied city. 部队从沦陷的城市安全撤出。 2. He immediately sounded a retreat. 他立刻下令撤退。 3. The minister made an undignified retreat from his earlier position. 那部长很不光彩地背离了他原先的立场。 4. The Senator made an embarrassing retreat from his earlier position. 这位参议员很尴尬地改变了他早先的立场。 5. After several reverses the enemy was forced to retreat. 几经失败之后，敌军被迫后撤。', '名词: retreater 过去式: retreated 过去分词: retreated 现在分词: retreating 第三人称单数: retreats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grieved', '[griːvd]', '伤心的', '1. The number of night elves pursuing their studies with the demigod dwindled, and Cenarius was grieved to realize that all his work had been for naught. 随着继续依据半神指导的暗夜精灵人数逐渐的减少，塞纳留斯伤心的意识到他所有的努力已经化为泡影。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('faint', '[feɪnt]', 'adj.微弱的；无力的；模糊的 v.昏倒 n.昏厥；昏倒', '1. A faint hope still flickered in her breast. 一种微弱的希望仍在她的心中闪动着。 2. He could discern a faint light ahead in the forest. 他能看到前面森林里有一线微弱的灯光。 3. I heard a faint sound in the distance. 我听到远处有个微弱的声音。 4. Every time I think of it I feel faint! 每次想到这些 5. You\'d better attend to that girl. I think she\'s going to faint. 你最好去照顾那女孩，我看她快昏倒了。 6. The little girl went off in a faint,but the doctor pulled her round very soon. 小女孩昏倒了，但医生很快使她苏醒过来。', '副词: faintly 比较级: fainter 最高级: faintest 名词: fainter 过去式: fainted 过去分词: fainted 现在分词: fainting 第三人称单数: faints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sermon', '[\'sɜːrmən]', 'n.布道；说教', '1. The minister preached a sermon on humility. 牧师就谦恭的问题布道。 2. Father gave me a sermon on table manners. 父亲就餐桌礼仪问题对我作了一番说教。 3. It is easier than the practice to deliver a sermon. 说教比实践更容易。', '形容词: sermonic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mosquito', '[mə\'skiːtoʊ]', 'n.蚊子', '1. The mosquito is the disgusting thing. 蚊子是讨厌的东西。 2. Mosquitoes like to suck the blood of people and animals. 蚊子喜好吸人和动物的血。 3. The mosquito is a transmitter of disease. 蚊子能传播疾病。', '名词复数: mosquitoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('doctrine', '[\'dɑːktrɪn]', 'n.学说；教义；主义；（政府政策的）正式声明', '1. This is the doctrine of the nominalist party. 这是唯名主义学派的学说。 2. Christian and Muslim doctrines are very different. 基督教教义和穆斯林教义极为不同。 3. He was impelled to proclaim his doctrine. 他不得不宣扬他的教义。 4. He preached a doctrine which was new to him. 他对教义的解释一改旧貌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('juice', '[dʒuːs]', 'n.果汁；肉汁；消化液；汽油；精力 vt.挤出汁来；使有活力', '1. I like to drink coconut juice. 我喜欢喝椰子汁。 2. She was drinking juice through a straw. 她正在用吸管喝果汁。 3. Give the bottle a couple of shakes before pouring the juice. 倒果汁前，先把瓶子摇几下。 4. Would you like some tomato juice? 你想要些番茄汁吗？ 5. She juiced an orange for her breakfast. 她用一只橙子榨汁作早餐饮料。', '过去式: juiced 过去分词: juiced 现在分词: juicing 第三人称单数: juices');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embezzle', '[ɪm\'bezl]', 'vt.盗用；挪用', '1. Associated press announces, will adopt law to act, make do to embezzle illegally the website of associated press news. 美联社宣布，将采取法律行动，对付非法盗用美联社新闻的网站。 2. Those who embezzle the interest of misappropriated public funds and those who are bribed to embezzle public funds should be seriously published. 侵吞挪用公款的利息和挪用公款而收受贿赂的应择一重罪处罚。', '名词: embezzlement 过去式: embezzled 过去分词: embezzled 现在分词: embezzling 第三人称单数: embezzles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('descent', '[dɪ\'sent]', 'n.下降；下坡；家世；血统；侵袭；衰落；继承', '1. There was a descent of temperature after rain. 雨后气温下降了。 2. The trail zigzagged down the abrupt descent of the canyon. 这条小路弯弯曲曲的顺着峡谷那陡削的下坡蜿蜒而下。 3. He traces his descent back to an old norman family. 他追踪自己的世系上溯至一个古老的诺曼家族。 4. Many Americans are of English descent. 许多美国人的祖籍是英国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('passage', '[\'pæsɪdʒ]', 'n.通过；通道；走廊；(文章等的)段落；(时间的)消逝', '1. The bridge is not strong enough to allow the passage of vehicles. 这座桥不够牢固，车辆不能通行。 2. The police kept a clear passage for the traffic. 警方使来往车辆畅通无阻。 3. We discovered a secret passage behind the wall. 我们在墙后发现了一个秘密通道。 4. This is our room, and yours is down the passage. 这是我们的房间，你们的在走廊的那一头。', '过去式: passaged 过去分词: passaged 现在分词: passaging 第三人称单数: passages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('election', '[ɪ\'lekʃn]', 'n.选举；当选；选举权', '1. Our party was routed at the election. 我们党在竞选中被彻底击败了。 2. I may vote for her at the next election. 下届选举我可能选她。 3. After the election the party was reduced to a rump. 选举之后，该党的党员所剩无几了。 4. The democrats hope to get back at the next election. 民主党希望在下次大选中重新执政。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abolish', '[ə\'bɑːlɪʃ]', 'vt.废除；革除；消灭', '1. Abraham Lincoln abolished slavery in the United States. 亚伯拉罕·林肯在美国废除了奴隶制。 2. There are many bad customs and laws that ought to be abolished. 有许多不良的习俗和法规应予以废除。 3. They petitioned the government to abolish hanging. 他们向政府请愿，要求废除绞刑。 4. The legislature passed a law to abolish the surtax. 立法机关通过了一项废除附加税的法令。', '形容词: abolishable 名词: abolisher 过去式: abolished 过去分词: abolished 现在分词: abolishing 第三人称单数: abolishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('approximate', '[ə\'prɑːksɪmət]', 'adj.近似的；大约的 v.接近；约等于', '1. This is just an approximate figure. 这仅仅是个近似值。 2. We are entirely justified in using the approximate theory. 我们用近似理论完全正当。 3. He spent approximate two hours searching the photo. 他用了大约两小时来寻找这张照片. 4. The approximate number of students in the school is 300. 这所学校的学生数大约为300人。 5. Production costs approximate to $100,000 . 生产成本接近十万美元。', '副词: approximately 过去式: approximated 过去分词: approximated 现在分词: approximating 第三人称单数: approximates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feud', '[fjuːd]', 'n.长期不和；争执 n.封地 v.长期斗争；结世仇', '1. The two tribes were long at feud with each other. 这两个部族长期不和。 2. Insults only served to inflame the feud. 侮辱只是起了加剧长期不和的作用。 3. The timing of the transaction raises questions about the status of Mr.Murdoch\'s feud with John C. 交易的时机使人对默多克与自由媒体主席马龙的争执状态产生疑问。 4. The barriers between Europe and Asia set up by the religious feud of Christianity and Islam were lowered. 欧亚之间因基督教和伊斯兰教这种宗教争执而树立的障碍逐步消除。 5. The two families have been at feud with each other. 两个家族之间有世仇。', '过去式: feuded 过去分词: feuded 现在分词: feuding 第三人称单数: feuds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emit', '[i\'mɪt]', 'vt.发出，发射；放射；吐露', '1. The cheese was emitting a strong smell. 干酪散发出强烈的气味。 2. A volcano emits smoke and ashes. 火山散发着烟和灰。 3. He was so pale that he seemed to emit a pearly glow. 他白得似乎发出像一样珍珠的微光。 4. Fireflies emit light but not heat. 萤火虫发光但不放出热。', '名词: emitter 过去式: emitted 过去分词: emitted 现在分词: emitting 第三人称单数: emits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commission', '[kə\'mɪʃn]', 'n.佣金；委员会；委托；委任；犯罪 vt.授予；使服役；委托', '1. Do not deduct any commission from the consignment value. 不要从货物的价值中扣除佣金。 2. The report was submitted to the commission for consideration. 这份报告已呈报委员会审批。 3. He had received the commission to build a new bridge over the river. 他受委托在这条河上建一座新桥。 4. We all approve of the commission of authority to him. 我们都赞成把职权委任於他。 5. He was commissioned captain of the United States Air Force. 他被授予美国空军上校。', '形容词: commissional 过去式: commissioned 过去分词: commissioned 现在分词: commissioning 第三人称单数: commissions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('divergent', '[daɪ\'vɜːdʒənt]', 'adj.分歧的；分开的；偏离的', '1. For the Jazz, the loss produced divergent viewpoints afterward. 失利后的爵士出现了很多有分歧的观点。 2. Not surprisingly, studies that try directly to measure the distributional consequences reach divergent conclusions. 试图直接估量分配结果而导致结论分歧的研究毫不奇怪。', '副词: divergently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aesthetic', '[es\'θetɪk]', 'adj.美学的；审美的；有美感的 n.(复数)审美观', '1. Later he also gained in aesthetic knowledge. 后来他的美学知识也增加了。 2. From an aesthetic point of view it\'s a thetic view. 从美学观点来说, 这是个武断的看法。 3. The professor advanced a new aesthetic theory. 那位教授提出了新的美学理论。 4. His aesthetic ideas were his own. 他有他自己的审美观念。 5. Natural aesthetic is the core of Chinese aesthetics. 自然审美是中国古代美学的核心。', '副词: aesthetically 异体字: esthetic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('parliament', '[\'pɑːrləmənt]', 'n.议会；国会；一届议会的会期', '1. Parliament will debate the nationalization issue next week. 议会将在下周辩论国有化议题。 2. He lost his seat in the Parliament at the election. 他在选举中失去了议会中的席位。 3. The Parliament decided to impeach the President. 国会决定弹劾总统。 4. Parliament has passed an Act forbidding the killing of rare animals. 国会通过了一项法令，禁止捕杀珍稀动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('satire', '[\'sætaɪər]', 'n.讽刺文；讽刺', '1. Satire is a high and subtle art. 讽刺是一门崇高而又含蓄的艺术。 2. Politicians are legitimate targets for satire. 政治家理所当然是讽刺的靶子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amid', '[ə\'mɪd]', 'prep.在其间；在其中', '1. He sat down amid deafening applause. 他在震耳欲聋的掌声中就坐。 2. I stood amid a sea of corn. 我站在茫茫一片庄稼之中。 3. He is amid his enemies. 他被敌人包围。 4. We groped amid the darkness. 我们在黑暗中摸索。', '异体字: amidst');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('formidable', '[\'fɔːrmɪdəbl]', 'adj.强大的；可怕的；难对付的', '1. He was one of the most formidable intellects of his time. 他是该时代的盖世奇才。 2. His mother is a most formidable lady. 他的母亲是个最令人生畏的妇人。 3. They climbed up the last part of the mountain in formidable weather conditions. 他们在恶劣的天气条件下登上了山的顶峰。 4. Martin is formidable. His left hook is devastating. 马丁很难对付，他的左钩拳极有威力。', '副词: formidably 名词: formidability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('internal', '[ɪn\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.国内的；内部的；身内的', '1. They were opposed to foreign involvement in their internal affairs. 他们反对外国参与他们本国内政。 2. He worked in internal trade. 他的工作是做国内贸易。 3. We should make an internal inquiry to find out who is responsible for the it. 我们应进行内部调查,找出对此事承担责任的人。 4. She\'s been having some internal problems. 她一直有些内科疾病。', '副词: internally 名词: internality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tackle', '[\'tækl]', 'v.处理；对付；阻截(对方球员)；与…交涉 n.滑车；用具；铲球；(美式足球)拦截手', '1. Can you suggest how we might tackle the problem? 我们怎样处理这问题，你能给出个主意吗? 2. I suggested to him that we should tackle the problem another way. 我向他建议我们用另一种方式处理这个问题。 3. I\'ll tackle the boss for a raise. 我将与老板交涉要求增加薪水。 4. If Bill is late again I will tackle him about it . 如果彼尔再迟到的话，我就得和他开诚布公地谈谈了。 5. The cupboard was stuffed with old fishing tackle. 小橱里塞满了旧的钓鱼用具。', '名词: tackler 过去式: tackled 过去分词: tackled 现在分词: tackling 第三人称单数: tackles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('explicit', '[ɪk\'splɪsɪt]', 'adj.明确的；清晰的；清楚的；露骨的', '1. They gave explicit reasons for leaving. 他们明确地说出了离开的原因。 2. A man can try his best to perfect and improve himself only if he has strong desires and explicit goal. 只有怀着强烈的欲望,有着明确的目标,一个人才能竭尽全力去完善自我,提升自我。 3. He has an explicit understanding of this. 他对这个了解得很清晰。 4. He gave me explicit directions on how to get there. 他清清楚楚地告诉我怎样到达那里。', '副词: explicitly 名词: explicitness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contribute', '[kən\'trɪbjuːt]', 'vt.捐助；投稿 vi.投稿；贡献；是原因之一', '1. It was generous of her to contribute such a large sum. 她很大方，捐助了这么大笔钱。 2. She asked him to contribute a biweekly article on European affairs. 她让他每两周写一篇有关欧洲情况的文章。 3. Don\'t contribute after the closing date. 请在截止日期前投稿。 4. It is an honour to be invited to contribute to your magazine. 应邀向贵杂志投稿是一个荣誉。', '形容词: contributive 副词: contributively 名词: contributiveness 过去式: contributed 过去分词: contributed 现在分词: contributing 第三人称单数: contributes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vehemence', '[\'viːəməns]', 'n.热烈；猛烈', '1. The attack increased in vehemence. 进攻越来越猛烈。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tropic', '[\'trɑːpɪk]', 'n.回归线；热带 adj.热带的', '1. The outside temperature in countries outside the Tropic belt is too volatile and too cold to allow the tree to develop. 在这条回归线带外边的国家的室外温度太易变并且太冷不能允许树生长。 2. She sorted out her things for tropic travel. 她整理热带旅行的东西。 3. The tropic sun glared down on us all day. 热带的太阳整日灼晒着我们。 4. The tropic sun glared down on us all day. 热带的太阳整日灼晒着我们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distressed', '[dɪ\'strest]', 'adj.痛苦的 动词distress的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He is the refuge of the distressed. 他是不幸者的朋友。 2. He is in bad, distressed circumstances. 他境遇贫困，生活痛苦。 3. What are you looking so distressed for? 什么事情使你看起来如此烦恼？ 4. I was most distressed to hear the sad news of your father\'s death. 我听到你父亲去世的噩耗，十分难过。 5. Her husband\'s death distressed her greatly. 她丈夫的去世使她很痛苦。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('touchy', '[\'tʌtʃi]', 'adj.易怒的；难以取悦的；敏感的', '1. He\'s an extremely touchy character and you have to handle him with kid gloves. 他是一个极易因小事而生气的人，因而你得温和灵巧地对待他。 2. He\'s a little touchy about his weight. 他对自己的体重感到有点儿苦恼。 3. He is in a particularly touchy mood today. 他今天情绪特别不好。 4. The mines are touchy as hell. 地雷非常灵敏，一有触动便会爆炸。', '副词: touchily 比较级: touchier 最高级: touchiest 名词: touchiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('encompass', '[ɪn\'kʌmpəs]', 'vt.围绕；包围；包括；完成', '1. The prison is encompassed by high walls. 监狱被高墙围绕着。 2. The voices of people and sounds of cars encompass his path. 他在路上听见四面八方都是人声车声。 3. The general arts at the university encompass a wide range of subjects. 大学文科包括的科目非常广泛。', '名词: encompassment 过去式: encompassed 过去分词: encompassed 现在分词: encompassing 第三人称单数: encompasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('justly', '[\'dʒʌstli]', 'adv.公正地；理由充分地；正当地', '1. They dealt with the problem justly. 他们公正地处理了这个问题。 2. We like our work to be justly evaluated. 我们喜欢别人公正的评价我们的工作。 3. His superior put in a word for him justly and he got the job. 他的上级为他说了句公正的话，他得到了那份工作。 4. He is justly called the Father of Texas. 他被誉为得克萨斯之父是当之无愧的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('violent', '[\'vaɪələnt]', 'adj.猛烈的；强烈的；暴力的；极端的', '1. The soldiers launched into a violent attack. 士兵们展开猛烈的攻击。 2. The violent blow sent him down on his knees. 那猛烈的一击使他跪倒在地。 3. She was in violent temper. 她暴跳如雷。 4. They showed violent opposition to the oppressor. 他们对压迫者表现出强烈的不满。', '副词: violently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spoil', '[spɔɪl]', 'v.宠坏；溺爱；破坏；腐坏；使索然无味 n.战利品；奖品', '1. A fond mother may spoil her child. 溺爱的母亲可能会宠坏她的孩子。 2. The child was spoilt by his grandfather. 这个孩子被他的爷爷给惯坏了。 3. The children kept quarreling and spoiled our holiday. 孩子们不断吵架，破坏了我们的假期。 4. He had spoiled the soup by putting in too much salt. 他往汤里放盐太多，把汤给糟蹋了。 5. The invaders made spoil of all in their way. 侵略者所到之处无不洗劫一空。', '过去式: spoiled/spoilt 过去分词: spoiled/spoilt 现在分词: spoiling 第三人称单数: spoils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acute', '[ə\'kjuːt]', 'adj.严重的；敏锐的；急性的；剧烈的', '1. He suffers from acute depression. 他患有严重的抑郁症。 2. This area has an acute shortage of water. 这个地方缺水严重。 3. She has acute hearing. 她有很敏锐的听力。 4. The doctor said that you had acute appendicitis. 医生说您患的是急性阑尾炎。', '副词: acutely 名词: acuteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corpulent', '[\'kɔːrpjələnt]', 'adj.肥胖的', '1. Sitting behind the window was a corpulent woman with a face of steel. 那窗口后面坐着一个面如镔铁的胖妇女。', '副词: corpulently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corrode', '[kə\'roʊd]', 'v.腐蚀；侵蚀；损害', '1. Iron corrodes easily. 铁易锈损。 2. This acid may corrode iron. 这种酸能腐蚀铁。 3. Certain chemicals will corrode if left on bare metal. 有些化学药品如留在裸露的金属上会起腐蚀作用。 4. The furniture should be of smooth, hard material not liable to warp or corrode. 家具应使用光滑、坚硬、不易变形和腐蚀的材料制作。', '形容词: corrodible 过去式: corroded 过去分词: corroded 现在分词: corroding 第三人称单数: corrodes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tremendous', '[trə\'mendəs]', 'adj.巨大的；惊人的', '1. He has a tremendous hold over his younger brother. 他对他弟弟很有影响。 2. She does her work with tremendous vigour. 她工作起来干劲十足。 3. The discovery caused a tremendous commotion in the scientific world. 那项发现在科学界引起极大的震动。 4. We got a tremendous surprise when she arrived. 她的到来使我们大吃一惊。', '副词: tremendously 名词: tremendousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idiosyncrasy', '[ˌɪdiə\'sɪŋkrəsi]', 'n.特质', '1. One of her little idiosyncrasies is always washing in cold water. 她有个怪习惯,就是洗什么都爱用冷水。 2. Eating no meat was Amy\'s idiosyncrasy. 不吃肉是艾美的习惯。 3. Personality is the supreme realization of the innate idiosyncrasy of a living being. 人格是生物内在特质的最高实现。', '形容词: idiosyncratic 副词: idiosyncratically 名词复数: idiosyncrasies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intrude', '[ɪn\'truːd]', 'v.闯入；侵入；打扰；干涉', '1. The angry visitor tried to intrude himself into the council meeting. 愤怒的来访者试图闯入会场。 2. He had no wish to intrude on their privacy. 他原本就不想触犯他们私人活动的自由。 3. A translator shouldn\'t intrude his own opinions into what he\'s translating. 译者不应该擅自把自己的意思加进译文中。 4. I don\'t want to intrude on you if you are very busy. 如果你很忙的话，我就不打扰了。', '名词: intruder 过去式: intruded 过去分词: intruded 现在分词: intruding 第三人称单数: intrudes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('giraffe', '[dʒə\'ræf]', 'n.长颈鹿', '1. The giraffe is much taller than the deer. 长颈鹿比鹿高多了。 2. The giraffe eats tender leaf from the tree highly. 长颈鹿从高高的树上吃掉嫩树叶子。 3. The giraffe must get up at six in the morning if it wants to have its breakfast in its stomach by nine. 长颈鹿得要在早上六点起来，如果它想早饭在九点钟之前到达胃里的话。', '形容词: giraffish 名词复数: giraffes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rapacious', '[rə\'peɪʃəs]', 'adj.贪婪的；强夺的', '1. Several of the Arab countries represented in the President\'s office needed the United States to fend off threats from rapacious neighbors. 有几个阿拉伯国家派人到总统办公室声称，它们需要美国的援助，来抵挡贪得无厌的邻国的威胁。 2. Hawks and other rapacious birds prey on variety of small animals. 老鹰和其他贪婪的鸟类捕食各种小动物。 3. Mr Brown said there was also a global perspective to America\'s rapacious model of consumption. 布朗先生说，还有一个研究美国掠夺资源模式的全球视角。', '副词: rapaciously 名词: rapacity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('textile', '[\'tekstaɪl]', 'n.纺织品', '1. He intends to retail textile goods. 他打算零售纺织品。 2. This textile feels like real leather. 这种纺织品摸上去象真皮似的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vehicle', '[\'viːɪkl]', 'n.车辆；交通工具；传播媒介；手段；工具', '1. No entry for vehicle! 禁止车辆入内！ 2. It is time for the yearly check of vehicle safety. 到车辆安全年审的时间了。 3. Subway is a convenient vehicle for those white collars. 地铁对于白领阶层来说是很方便的交通工具。 4. Television has become an important vehicle for spreading political ideas. 电视已成为传播政治思想的重要媒介。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('luxury', '[\'lʌkʃəri]', 'n.奢侈品；奢侈；豪华', '1. The increasing sale of luxury goods is an index of the country\'s prosperity. 奢侈商品销售量日增是该国繁荣的标志。 2. The government has imposed strict controls over the import of luxury goods. 政府对奢侈品的进口采取了严格的管制。 3. If he can afford a luxury yacht, then a fortiori he can afford to pay his debts. 他若能买得起豪华的快艇，就更能匀出钱来还债了。 4. In old society, the gentry lived in luxury. 在旧社会，贵族们生活奢侈。', '名词复数: luxuries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('property', '[\'prɑːpərti]', 'n.财产；所有物；地产，房地产；性质；道具', '1. The property was returned to the original owner. 财产已归还原主。 2. But you do not have the right to initiate force against the life, liberty and property of others. 但是,你没有发起强占其他人生命,自由和所有物的权利。 3. He has a large property in the county. 他在这个县有一大片地产。 4. Cheerfulness is a property of her personality. 开朗乐观是她的性格特征。', '形容词: propertyless 名词复数: properties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barrier', '[\'bæriər]', 'n.栅栏；障碍物；屏障', '1. The ice skater rammed into the barrier. 溜冰者撞到护栏上了。 2. Heavy duties on imports and exports are a barrier to international trade. 进出口的高关税是国际贸易的障碍。 3. The Sahara Desert is a natural barrier between north and central Africa. 撒哈拉沙漠是北非与中非之间的天然屏障。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('naughty', '[\'nɔːti]', 'adj.顽皮的；淘气的；不妥的', '1. His dog scared that naughty boy away. 他的狗把那个顽皮的孩子吓走了。 2. You naughty boy! I\'ve told you not to play in the street. 你这顽皮孩子！我说过，叫你别在马路上玩。 3. This naughty boy is really troublesome. 这个淘气的男孩子真是惹人烦。 4. The naughty boy hid the books in the shrub. 这个淘气的孩子把书藏在了灌木丛里。', '副词: naughtily 比较级: naughtier 最高级: naughtiest 名词: naughtiness 名词复数: naughties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cover', '[\'kʌvər]', 'n.封面；盖子；套子；表面 v.覆盖；涉及；包含；掩护；给…保险', '1. The front cover of the novel has been torn off. 这本小说的封面已被撕掉。 2. I can\'t make the cover of the tin fit on. 我无法把这罐头的盖子盖上。 3. The car should be housed with a cover for a longer time\'s parking. 长时间的存放汽车，应给汽车罩上套子。 4. Tooth-colored porcelain will cover the metal crowns. 金属表面覆盖和牙齿一样颜色地瓷。 5. Snow covered the ground. 积雪覆盖了大地。', '形容词: coverable 名词: coverer 过去式: covered 过去分词: covered 现在分词: covering 第三人称单数: covers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flicker', '[\'flɪkər]', 'n.闪烁；闪光；颤动 v.闪动；闪烁；摇动', '1. She is read by the flicker light of the candle. 她借著闪烁的烛光读书。 2. Watch the flames flicker in the room. 注视着火焰在屋里闪烁。 3. But the tiny flicker of Gryffindor boldness wasn\'t entirely quenched. 但是，格兰芬多的胆大冒失的微小闪光并没有完全熄灭。 4. Now as Peter\'s eyes discovered the bandaid on his neck, the telltale flicker of anger appeared. 现在彼得一看到他脖子上的绷带，那怒火的隐蔽闪光就出现了。 5. Perhaps there\'s a brief flicker in some toolbar button which, when investigated, reveals a crash. 可能在工具条的一个短暂的闪动，经过调查后，揭示了一个失效错误。', '过去式: flickered 过去分词: flickered 现在分词: flickering 第三人称单数: flickers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('analogous', '[ə\'næləɡəs]', 'adj.类似的', '1. The human heart is analogous to a pump. 人的心脏和泵类似。 2. Brains and computers are often considered analogous. 人脑和电脑常被认为是类似的。', '副词: analogously 名词: analogousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('continuum', '[kən\'tɪnjʊəm]', 'n.连续；连续统；闭连集', '1. The results prove that Continuum Damage Mechanics model can describe the cumulation and development of damage more accurately. 分析结果表明，连续损伤模型能更合理地描述材料蠕变损伤的累积发展过程。', '名词复数: continua');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dated', '[\'deɪtɪd]', 'adj.过时的；陈旧的 动词date的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Many dated expressions are being dropped from the new dictionary. 这本新词典中删去了很多过时的词语。 2. She uses rather dated words and phrases. 她使用的词语未免太陈旧了。', '副词: datedly 名词: datedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rally', '[\'ræli]', 'n.集会；（价值等）回升；回合 vi.重整旗鼓；恢复精神；(人)集合起来 vt.嘲弄；重新召集；激励', '1. They will hold a peace rally. 他们要举行一个拥护和平的大会。 2. Countless people joined the rally at the square. 不计其数的人参加了广场上的集会。 3. After a brief rally share fall back to a new low. 股票经过一次短暂回升后回落到一个新的低点。 4. His sudden rally surprised the doctor. 他的突然复元使医生大为惊奇。 5. The team was thrown onto the defensive as their opponents rallied. 该队在对手重整旗鼓后,被迫采取守势。 6. The commander was able to rally the fleeing troops. 指挥官能够重整其溃散的部队。', '名词复数: rallies 过去式: rallied 过去分词: rallied 现在分词: rallying 第三人称单数: rallies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('logical', '[\'lɑːdʒɪkl]', 'adj.符合逻辑的；逻辑上的；合理的', '1. Every argument was stated with logical precision. 每一个论点都阐述得精确严密，符合逻辑。 2. You must learn how to construct a logical argument. 你必须学会怎样确立合乎逻辑的论点。 3. My argument follows the rules of logical induction. 我是遵循逻辑归纳的法则进行论证的。 4. The article has a logical composition. 这篇文章布局合理。', '副词: logically 名词: logicality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('query', '[\'kwɪri]', 'n.疑问；质问；疑问号 vt.质问；对 ... 表示怀疑', '1. Your interesting report raises several important queries. 你的精彩报告引出了几个重要问题。 2. I send all my income tax query to my accountant. 我把所有有关所得税的疑问送交会计师。 3. Put a query. 打一个问号。 4. The minister was queried about his plans for the industry. 有人向部长提出了工业计划问题。', '名词: querier 名词复数: queries 过去式: queried 过去分词: queried 现在分词: querying 第三人称单数: queries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obstacle', '[\'ɑːbstəkl]', 'n.障碍；绊脚石', '1. Lack of education is an obstacle of success. 缺乏教育是成功的障碍。 2. This is the chief obstacle to world peace. 这是世界和平的主要障碍。 3. He took every obstacle in his stride. 他轻易地度过一切难关。 4. Overstaffing has become the obstacle for reforms. 人浮于事已成为改革的绊脚石。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extol', '[ɪk\'stoʊl]', 'v.颂扬；称赞', '1. The general was extolled as the man who had led the country to victory. 这位将军被誉为领导全国赢得胜利的人。 2. He keeps extolling her goodness. 他对她的善良赞不绝口。 3. They extol the virtues of the peaceful life. 对于农村宁静生活的美处，他们称赞不已。', '名词: extoller');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('authority', '[ə\'θɔːrəti]', 'n.权力；官方；当局；职权；权威', '1. The government is the highest authority in the country. 政府是国家的最高权力机构。 2. Authorities say the fires do look suspicious. 官方表示，火灾看起来确实很奇怪。 3. Both the authorities and the media wondered whether insider dealing had been going on. 官方跟媒体都在怀疑这里面是不是存在内幕交易。 4. The authorities did not interfere with us. 当局不干涉我们。', '名词复数: authorities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boring', '[\'bɔːrɪŋ]', 'adj.令人厌烦的；乏味的', '1. It is awfully boring. 太叫人厌烦了。 2. It is boring to listen to the same story. 听相同的故事是令人厌烦的。 3. His long boring story made me yawn. 他的冗长的故事听得我直打呵欠。 4. He gave a boring speech full of stale jokes. 他的发言很乏味,满是陈腐的笑话。', '副词: boringly 名词: boringness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hook', '[hʊk]', 'n.钩；钩状物；勾拳 v.钩住；弯成(钩状)；当妓女', '1. Please hang your coat on the hook. 请把你的外衣挂在钩上。 2. They took the phone off the hook so no calls would disturb them. 他们摘下电话听筒，以免电话打扰他们。 3. He smote his match to the ground with a left hook. 他以一记左钩拳把对手击倒在地。 4. Please hook the rope over the nail. 请把绳子挂在那根钉子上。', '过去式: hooked 过去分词: hooked 现在分词: hooking 第三人称单数: hooks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tornado', '[tɔːr\'neɪdoʊ]', 'n.龙卷风；飓风；旋风', '1. The entire village was obliterated by the tornado. 整个村庄被龙卷风摧毁了。 2. The tornado cut a swath through the town. 龙卷风袭击该镇,留下一长条破坏的痕迹。 3. When a tornado touches the ground, it does a lot of damage. 当飓风到达地面时，它会带来许多灾难。 4. The ruin of the house was caused by a violent tornado. 一阵猛烈的旋风把房屋卷倒了。', '形容词: tornadic 名词复数: tornadoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blossom', '[\'blɑːsəm]', 'n.花；开花；全盛期 vi.开花；成长', '1. The sunshine will bring out the blossom. 阳光将使花朵开放。 2. The tree was covered with beautiful pink blossom. 这树开满了美丽的粉红色的花。 3. The apple trees are in blossom. 苹果树正在开花。 4. There are many pear trees covered in blossom. 那里有许多开满花的梨树。 5. The apple trees are blossoming. 苹果树正在开花。', '形容词: blossomy 过去式: blossomed 过去分词: blossomed 现在分词: blossoming 第三人称单数: blossoms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deliver', '[dɪ\'lɪvər]', 'v.递送；发表（演讲）；交付；解救；生（孩子）；接生；履行；投掷', '1. The mailman delivers letters and parcels every morning. 邮差每天早晨递送信件和包裹。 2. He delivered a long prose. 他发表了一篇冗长乏味的演讲。 3. We deliver the goods in batches. 我们分批交付货物。 4. Education delivered him from ignorance. 教育把他从无知中解救出来。', '形容词: deliverable 名词: deliverability 过去式: delivered 过去分词: delivered 现在分词: delivering 第三人称单数: delivers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sedate', '[sɪ\'deɪt]', 'adj.安静的；镇静的 vt.使安静；使镇静', '1. A sedate color scheme calls for an obvious place for the eye to rest. 一个安静的配色方案需要为眼睛提供一个显著的休息的地方。', '副词: sedately 名词: sedateness 过去式: sedated 过去分词: sedated 现在分词: sedating 第三人称单数: sedates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gasoline', '[\'ɡæsəliːn]', 'n.<美>汽油 亦写作gasolene', '1. The car is short of gasoline. 汽车的汽油不够了。 2. Our gasoline has been used up. 我们的汽油用完了。 3. Gasoline drained slowly from the tilted can. 煤油慢慢从倾斜的油罐里流出来 4. The plant converts crude oil into gasoline. 这家工厂将原油加工成汽油。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unfair', '[ˌʌn\'fer]', 'adj.不公平的；(商业上)不正当的', '1. The detention of the whole class was unfair. 滞留全班学生是不公平的。 2. It\'s unfair to devalue anyone\'s work unjustly. 不公正地贬低任何人的工作都是不公平的。', '副词: unfairly 比较级: unfairer 最高级: unfairest 名词: unfairness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brutal', '[\'bruːtl]', 'adj.野蛮的；残暴的', '1. The people have been kept down for years by a brutal regime. 人民多年遭受野蛮制度压迫。 2. The enemy made a brutal attack upon the villagers. 敌人对村民们进行了野蛮的攻击。 3. NATO\'s invasion of this independent country is a brutal violation of human rights. 北约对这个独立的国家的侵略是对人权的野蛮侵犯。 4. The brutal soldiers beat their prisoners ruthlessly. 残暴的士兵野蛮地抽打俘虏。', '副词: brutally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('illusion', '[ɪ\'luːʒn]', 'n.错觉；幻觉；错误的信仰(或观念)', '1. Mirrors in a room often give an illusion of space. 房间里的镜子常给人一种空间增大的错觉。 2. A mirage is an optical illusion. 海市蜃楼是一种视错觉。 3. I thought I saw a ghost but it was just an optical illusion. 我以为我看见鬼了，其实只是一种幻觉。 4. This creates an illusion of variety. 这造成了一种多样化的幻觉。', '形容词: illusional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comic', '[\'kɑːmɪk]', 'n.连环图画；喜剧演员 adj.滑稽的；有趣的；喜剧的', '1. Children like to read comics. 孩子们喜欢看连环漫画。 2. He is looking for his comic book. 他在找他的连环画。 3. He is a popular TV comic. 他是观众喜爱的电视喜剧演员。 4. The comic scenes in the play were overdone. 这剧的滑稽场面太夸张了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('describe', '[dɪ\'skraɪb]', 'vt.描述；说成；形容；画(尤指几何图形)', '1. The police asked me to describe exactly how it happened. 警察让我描述一下这事是怎样发生的。 2. Words cannot describe the beauty of the scene. 语言难以描述那景色之美丽。 3. He describes himself as a doctor. 他自称是医生。 4. No one could describe the scorn of her expression. 谁也无法形容她那股鄙夷万分的表情。', '形容词: describable 名词: describer 过去式: described 过去分词: described 现在分词: describing 第三人称单数: describes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('benign', '[bɪ\'naɪn]', 'adj.仁慈的；温和的；良性的', '1. My mother\'s character is very benign. 我母亲非常慈祥。 2. The heat, the bureaucracy, the confusion and complications of his job, had reduced him in seven years to a blob of benign jelly. 炎热的天气，官僚政治和他工作的错综复杂和混乱，在七个年头里已使他变成一个仁慈的和稀泥老手。 3. The benign weather brought North America a bumper crop. 温和的气候给北美带来大丰收。 4. After tests the tumor was found to be benign. 检测发现肿瘤是良性的。', '副词: benignly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scoop', '[skuːp]', 'n.铲子；勺；舀取；穴；独家新闻 vt.挖空；舀取；抢先报道（获得）', '1. he used a scoop to serve the ice cream. 他用铲子来吃冰激凌。 2. There are several scoops in my kitchen. 我的厨房里有好几个勺子。 3. The newspaper got a scoop on the airplane crash. 该报独家报导了那次飞机失事。 4. This small rodent can scoop a long , narrow tunnel in a very short time . 这只海狸能在短时间内挖出一条长且窄的洞。', '名词: scooper 过去式: scooped 过去分词: scooped 现在分词: scooping 第三人称单数: scoops');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('divert', '[daɪ\'vɜːrt]', 'v.转移；娱乐', '1. A loud noise diverted my attention. 一阵喧闹声转移了我们的注意力。 2. They diverted the river to supply water to the town. 他们使河流改道以便向城市供水。 3. She dished up the anti-pollution business to divert the attention of the public. 她把防止污染的事情说得十分重要,以便转移公众的注意。 4. I found a computer game to divert the children. 我发现了一种供孩子娱乐的电脑游戏。', '副词: divertingly 名词: diverter 过去式: diverted 过去分词: diverted 现在分词: diverting 第三人称单数: diverts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commitment', '[kə\'mɪtmənt]', 'n.承诺；保证；信奉；献身；委任；交押', '1. If you are serious about our relationship, you should make a commitment. 如果你对我们的关系很认真，你就应该给个承诺。 2. He made a commitment to pay the rent on time. 他保证按时付房租。 3. It saddens me to recall that I assured him that I had no expectations of a long-term commitment. 现在回想起来，我为我一开始就向他保证说我也不期望一段长期的关系而伤感。 4. It has been argued that this anticipated the punctuated equilibrium hypothesis, but other scholars have preferred to emphasise Darwin\'s commitment to gradualism. 有人认为这加快了间断平衡假说的发展，但其他学者倾向于强调这表明了达尔文对渐进论的信奉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('garbage', '[\'ɡɑːrbɪdʒ]', 'n.垃圾；废物；食物残渣', '1. Please put the garbage in the dustbin. 请把垃圾放在桶里。 2. She threw the leftovers in the garbage. 她把剩饭倒进垃圾桶。 3. The smell of the garbage overpowered me. 垃圾的臭味使我无法忍受。 4. You are a garbage! 你真是个废物！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('varied', '[\'verid]', 'adj.各种各样的 动词vary的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Yet, outdoor activities are varied and tempting in the U.S.A. 而各种各样的户外活动在美国则引人入胜。 2. Varied motives prompt people to join a political party. 各种各样的动机促使人们加入政党。', '副词: variedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('photodissociation', '[ˌfoʊtoʊdɪˌsoʊsɪ\'eɪʃən]', 'n.光致离解(光解作用)', '1. All the atomic and molecular systems are subject to photoionization and photodissociation. 所有的原子和分子系统都受光致电离和光致离解的影响。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('upheaval', '[ʌp\'hiːvl]', 'n.向上的运动；剧变；动乱', '1. The French Revolution was a volcanic upheaval in European history. 法国大革命是欧洲历史上的一次剧变。 2. It was a terrible upheaval when his father died. 他父亲去世时家里一团糟。 3. I can\'t face the upheaval of moving house again. 我无法忍受再次搬家的折腾。 4. Many years ago, Johnson faced a major upheaval in his life. 许多年前，约翰逊遭遇生命中的剧变。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enchant', '[ɪn\'tʃænt]', 'v.施魔法；使迷惑；使喜悦；使陶醉', '1. The act of enchanting. 使用魔法迷惑的行为 2. Enchanting as if with a magic spell; fascinating. 令人心醉的使如同有魔咒般迷住的; 迷人的 3. She was enchanted with the flowers you sent her. 她非常喜欢你送的花。', '过去式: enchanted 过去分词: enchanted 现在分词: enchanting 第三人称单数: enchants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('banner', '[\'bænər]', 'n.横幅；旗帜；大标题 adj.杰出的；特别好的 vt.用横幅装饰；以大标题报道', '1. Can you read that banner from this distance? 从这里你能看清那个横幅标语吗? 2. Do not use excessive banner advertisements. 不要使用过多的横幅广告。 3. The banner lent color to the streets. 旗帜给街道增添了色彩。 4. The patriots fought under the banner of freedom. 爱国者在自由的旗帜下战斗。 5. This year is a banner year for crops. 今年是个丰年。 6. The report was bannered by the People\'s Daily. 《人民日报》用横贯全页的大标题形式进行了报道。', '过去式: bannered 过去分词: bannered 现在分词: bannering 第三人称单数: banners');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('robust', '[roʊ\'bʌst]', 'adj.强健的；稳固的；耐用的；粗野的；浓的', '1. She was almost 90, but still very robust. 她将近90岁了，但身体仍然十分强健。 2. But I can say for sure that our monetary system is robust. 但是,我可以很肯定地讲,我们的货币体系是稳固。 3. He bought a robust metal cabinet for his new house. 他为新家购置了一个坚固耐用的金属柜。 4. He is a man with a rather robust sense of humor. 他具备颇为粗俗的幽默感。', '副词: robustly 名词: robustness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confidential', '[ˌkɑːnfɪ\'denʃl]', 'adj.秘密的；机密的；表示信任的；获信赖的', '1. He has been on confidential missions to Berlin. 他前往柏林执行秘密任务。 2. He told me the confidential information. 他向我透露了这个秘密的信息。 3. He was an author whose works were so little known as to be almost confidential. 他这位作家的著作是如此不为人所知，以致几乎等于机密文件。 4. Don\'t be too confidential with strangers. 不要过份相信陌生人。', '副词: confidentially 名词: confidentiality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scheme', '[skiːm]', 'n.阴谋；计划；方案 v.图谋；设计；策划；<非正式>认为', '1. Their scheme was exposed. 他们的阴谋被暴露了。 2. The police have uncovered a scheme of robbery. 警察当局破获了一起阴谋抢劫案。 3. They were bitterly opposed to the scheme. 他们强烈反对这个计划。 4. I rather doubt if such an ambitious scheme could be made a success of. 我真怀疑这样一个雄心勃勃的计划是否会成功。 5. He is scheming for power. 他在图谋争权。', '名词: schemer 过去式: schemed 过去分词: schemed 现在分词: scheming 第三人称单数: schemes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cancel', '[\'kænsl]', 'v.取消；作废；注销；抵消；删除 n.取消；删除', '1. The match had to be cancelled due to the bad weather. 比赛因天气不好只得取消。 2. If the worst comes to the worst, we\'ll have to cancel our holiday plans. 要是情况不妙，我们就只好取消度假计划了。 3. I\'ve lost my crdit card, so I have to go to the bank to cancel it. 我的信用卡弄丢了,我得去银行申请作废。 4. The ticket shall be cancelled once you enter the cinema. 你一进入电影院后,这张票就得注销了。', '形容词: cancelable 名词: canceler 过去式: canceled/cancelled 过去分词: canceled/cancelled 现在分词: canceling/cancelling 第三人称单数: cancels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('democratic', '[ˌdemə\'krætɪk]', 'adj.民主的；民主党的；大众的', '1. Many people were elected to take part in democratic involvement. 很多人被选举参与民主管理。 2. If we want to live a peaceful and democratic life, we must object to wars. 如果我们要过和平与民主的生活,就必须要反对战争。 3. She ran for office on the Democratic ticket. 她作为民主党的候选人参加竞选。 4. He threw a vote for the Democratic candidate. 他投了民主党总统候选人一票。', '副词: democratically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('congressman', '[\'kɑːŋɡrəsmən]', 'n.国会议员', '1. The Congressman of the district must be petitioned. 必须向区国会议员申请。 2. The congressman dressed up his statements to deceive the voters. 那个国会议员用花言巧语来欺骗选民。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plaster', '[\'plæstər]', 'n.石膏；灰泥；膏药 v.涂以灰泥；敷以膏药；使 ... 平', '1. His broken leg was encased in plaster. 他折的腿打上了石膏。 2. They closed the cracks in the wall with plaster. 他们用石膏把墙上的裂缝填满了。 3. This plaster may crack when it dries. 这种灰泥变干时可能会龟裂。 4. The plaster had started to come away from the wall. 灰泥已经开始从墙上脱落。 5. Will it take long to plaster the ceiling? 把天花板涂上灰泥要花很长时间吗?', '形容词: plastery 名词: plasterer 过去式: plastered 过去分词: plastered 现在分词: plastering 第三人称单数: plasters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('voyage', '[\'vɔɪɪdʒ]', 'n.航行；旅程 v.航行；旅行', '1. This is the virgin voyage of the ship. 这是这艘船的处女航。 2. The ship hit heavy fog on its voyage. 船在航行时碰上了大雾。 3. She went on a long sea voyage. 她乘船在海上长途旅行。 4. Once the voyage comes to an end. 旅程结束之际。 5. My dream is to voyage around the world in a hot air balloon. 我的梦想是乘着热气球周游世界。', '名词: voyager 过去式: voyaged 过去分词: voyaged 现在分词: voyaging 第三人称单数: voyages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dart', '[dɑːrt]', 'n.飞镖；投射；突进；缝褶 vi.快速投掷；突然移动 vt.使突然移动', '1. My blood rages like a dart. 我血液狂奔有如飞镖。 2. In the first there is often a dart board, 在普通酒吧里，通常有一个飞镖盘， 3. The boy hit the target with his first dart. 那男孩第一镖就击中了目标。 4. He made a sudden dart at his opponent. 他向对手做出突然的飞奔。 5. The sun darts forth its beams. 阳光四射。 6. She darted an angry look at her sister. 她生气地向她妹妹瞥了一眼。', '过去式: darted 过去分词: darted 现在分词: darting 第三人称单数: darts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('melt', '[melt]', 'vi.融化；熔化；消散 vt.使融化；使熔化；使消散 n.熔化物；融化；熔解', '1. These chocolates really melt in your mouth. 这些巧克力真正是入口即化。 2. His heart melted when he saw the little girl crying. 看到这个小女孩哭起来，他的心软了。 3. If you warm ice it will melt into water. 如果你把冰加热，它会融化成水。 4. Metals will melt when heated to a certain temperature. 金属加热到一定的温度都会熔化。 5. The sun melted the snow. 太阳使雪融化。 6. If you warm ice it will melt into water. 如果你把冰加热，它会融化成水。', '形容词: meltable 副词: meltingly 名词: meltability 过去式: melted 过去分词: melted 现在分词: melting 第三人称单数: melts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('penicillin', '[ˌpenɪ\'sɪlɪn]', 'n.青霉素', '1. He gave me a second shot of penicillin. 他又给我打了一针青霉素。 2. The nurse injected penicillin into her arm. 护士给她的胳膊注射了青霉素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('temporal', '[\'tempərəl]', 'adj.现世的；暂时的；当时的；太阳穴的；颞的', '1. He cares for nothing but temporal affairs. 他只关心世俗之事。 2. The Pope has no temporal power in modern society. 教皇在当代社会没有世俗方面的权利。 3. Temporal isolation appears to be possible. 暂时隔离是可行的。 4. Place your sword upon the ground, and rest in the temporal peace. 放下你的剑吧，静享这暂时的和平。', '副词: temporally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('petroleum', '[pə\'troʊliəm]', 'n.石油', '1. Indonesia is abundant in petroleum deposits. 印尼的石油蕴藏量丰富。 2. Petroleum can be used to produce various chemical products. 石油可用于生产多种化学产品。 3. Any new source of energy will be welcome, as there is a shortage of petroleum. 由于石油短缺，任何一种新能源都会受欢迎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('protein', '[\'proʊtiːn]', 'n.蛋白质', '1. You need more protein to build you up. 你需要增加蛋白质以增强体质。 2. Try to balance your diet by eating more fruit and less protein. 多吃些水果，少摄入些蛋白质，使饮食均衡合理。 3. Pulses are a good source of protein for vegetarians. 对于素食者来说,豆类食物是蛋白质的理想来源。 4. A vegetarian gets protein not from meat but from its analogues. 素食者所摄取的蛋白质不是来自肉类而是来自近似肉类的食物。', '形容词: proteinaceous');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barge', '[bɑːrdʒ]', 'n.驳船 vi.猛撞；冲；闯 vt.以驳船载运', '1. They sank the barge by making a hole in the bottom. 他们在驳船底部打个洞把它弄沉了。 2. People on the barge looked rather happy. 游船上的人们看上去很高兴。 3. He barged past me in the queue. 我在排队时他在我面前硬挤过去了。 4. How rude of you to barge into the conversation! 你打断人家的谈话，多没礼貌啊！', '过去式: barged 过去分词: barged 现在分词: barging 第三人称单数: barges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comet', '[\'kɑːmət]', 'n.彗星', '1. That comet is invisible to the unaided eye. 那颗彗星只用肉眼是看不到的。 2. Comets move around the sun like planets, but in long oval course. 彗星象行星一样绕太阳运转，然而其轨道呈狭长的椭圆形。', '形容词: cometary');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('guileless', '[\'ɡaɪlləs]', 'adj.不狡猾的；诚实的', '1. He is a guileless young man. 他是个诚实的年轻人。 2. He was very guileless in affiliating with people. 与人交往，他非常朴实。 3. She gave him a guileless look, but he knew he couldn\'t really trust her. 她朝他诚恳地看了一眼，但是他知道他不能真正地相信她。', '副词: guilelessly 名词: guilelessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('standard', '[\'stændərd]', 'n.标准；规格；水准；军旗 adj.标准的；普通的；规范的；权威的', '1. There is no absolute standard for beauty. 美是没有绝对的标准的。 2. More than 300 watches are not up to standard. 有300多块手表不合质量标准。 3. The government has an official standard for the purity of silver. 政府对于银的纯度定有官方的规格。 4. Washing machines have standard measurements to fit under kitchen units. 洗衣机的长宽高都有一定的规格，这样才能和厨房家具成为一体。 5. According to my height, what is my standard weight? 根据我的身高,我的标准体重是多少?', '副词: standardly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manual', '[\'mænjuəl]', 'adj.手工的；体力的 n.指南；手册；键盘', '1. Work done by machines has replaced manual labour. 机器生产已经代替了手工劳作。 2. Making small models requires manual skill. 制作小模型要手巧。 3. Having grown up in the countryside, I\'m used to manual labor. 我生长在农村,习惯体力劳动了。 4. This manual is full of useful tips. 这本小册子里有很多实用的小建议。', '副词: manually');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indecent', '[ɪn\'diːsnt]', 'adj.下流的；不妥当的', '1. It is indecent to say that. 说那样的话是很不礼貌的。 2. She accused him of making indecent suggestions to her. 她指控他对她有过下流的要求。 3. The deletion of all passages is considered to be indecent. 删除所有段落是不妥当的。', '副词: indecently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('license', '[\'laɪsns]', 'n.许可证；执照；特许 vt.发许可证给；特许', '1. We contemplate obtaining a technical license. 我们希望获得一项技术许可证。 2. His license was suspended for six months. 他的执照被吊销6个月。 3. The designers were allowed a lot of creative license. 那些设计者们获得了很多创意许可。 4. Are you licensed to drive? 你得到驾车的执照了吗？', '形容词: licensable 名词: licenser 过去式: licensed 过去分词: licensed 现在分词: licensing 第三人称单数: licenses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intimate', '[\'ɪntɪmət]', 'adj.亲密的；私人的；关系紧密的 vt.暗示；透露 n.密友', '1. She was so kind as to forgive her intimate friend who had betrayed her when she was in a great difficulty. 她如此善良,竟能原谅在她处境最艰难时背叛她的挚友。 2. The magazine published intimate details of their affair. 这本杂志刊登出了他们恋情的私密细节。 3. Island communities commonly feel an intimate connection with the sea and with seafarers. 岛国的居民一般都会感觉自己与海洋和水手之间存在着紧密的联系。 4. He stated what others had only dared to intimate. 他说出了别人只敢暗示的话。 5. Sir Reginald was known to his intimates as \"Porky\". 雷金纳德爵士的至交都叫他“胖子”。', '副词: intimately 名词: intimateness 过去式: intimated 过去分词: intimated 现在分词: intimating 第三人称单数: intimates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yen', '[jen]', 'n.日元 n.上瘾 vi.对 ... 上瘾', '1. I gave the beggar as much as 1,000 yen. 我给了这乞丐整整一千日元。 2. Please exchange twenty thousand yen into dollars. 请将两万日元换成美金。 3. She\'s developed a yen for detective stories. 她看侦探小说看上瘾了。', '名词复数: yen 过去式: yenned 过去分词: yenned 现在分词: yenning 第三人称单数: yens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frigid', '[\'frɪdʒɪd]', 'adj.寒冷的；冷淡的；(指女性)性冷淡的', '1. Huhhot is a frigid city in winter. 冬天的呼和浩特是一个寒冷的城市。 2. Frigid winds blew from the north. 寒风从北方吹来。 3. His frigid glance made me afraid. 他那冷淡的目光让我害怕。 4. She returned his smile with a frigid glance. 对他的微笑她报以冷冷的一瞥。', '副词: frigidly 名词: frigidity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('telescope', '[\'telɪskoʊp]', 'n.望远镜 v.缩短；压缩；套叠', '1. He saw a hungry wolf on the prowl with his telescope. 他通过望远镜看到了一头四处觅食的饿狼。 2. What is the range of this telescope? 这架望远镜的有效距离多大? 3. He was too poor to buy an astronomical telescope. 他太穷了，买不起天文望远镜。 4. I suggest we telescope the seminar into an hour. 我建议将研讨会缩短为一个小时。', '过去式: telescoped 过去分词: telescoped 现在分词: telescoping 第三人称单数: telescopes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ignorant', '[\'ɪɡnərənt]', 'adj.无知的；愚昧的；不知道的', '1. He\'s so ignorant that he cannot write his own name. 他很无知，连自己的名字都写不出。 2. She regarded her critics as ignorant and prejudiced. 她认为那些批评她的人既无知又存有偏见。 3. Ignorant children sometimes laugh at beggars and tramps. 无知的孩子们有时会嘲笑乞丐和无家可归的人。 4. His ignorant behaviour at the dinner table caused much embarrassment. 他在餐桌上举止粗鲁，在座的人颇为难堪。', '副词: ignorantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blur', '[blɜːr]', 'v.弄脏；使 ... 模糊 n.污点；模糊', '1. The damp paper caused the ink to blur. 潮纸因墨水弄上污渍。 2. Don\'t blur the distinctions between things. 不要模糊事物之间的差别。 3. Do drunkards blur reality, or come closer to it? 酒醉之后是使现实模糊不清，还是更加接近现实了呢? 4. But we see it only as a hazy blur. 但我们看到的只是模糊的斑点。', '形容词: blurry 名词: blurriness 过去式: blurred 过去分词: blurred 现在分词: blurring 第三人称单数: blurs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corps', '[kɔːr]', 'n.军团；兵团；队', '1. They were then beating up volunteers for the corps. 当时他们正在为军团募集志愿兵。 2. The Ministry of National Defence has recently embodied the troops in army corps. 最近国防部把军队编成了兵团. 3. The Marine Corps began to slim down under budget restrictions. 由于预算的限制，海军陆战队开始裁员。', '名词复数: corps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('permit', '[pər\'mɪt]', 'n.许可证；执照 v.允许；许可', '1. You can\'t work here without a work permit. 你没有许可证就不能在这里工作。 2. He said that if he had a permit he could get a job. 他说如果他有执照就能找到工作。 3. I\'ll come after the meeting if time permits. 如果时间许可的话，我开完会就来。 4. You are not permitted to smoke here. 此处不许吸烟。', '名词: permittee 过去式: permitted 过去分词: permitted 现在分词: permitting 第三人称单数: permits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defraud', '[dɪ\'frɔːd]', 'v.诈骗', '1. He defrauded the author of his property. 他把这个作家的财产骗走了。 2. She was charged with intent to defraud. 她被指控犯有蓄意诈骗钱财罪。', '名词: defraudation 过去式: defrauded 过去分词: defrauded 现在分词: defrauding 第三人称单数: defrauds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confront', '[kən\'frʌnt]', 'vt.对抗；遭遇；面临', '1. We must confront future with optimism. 我们必须乐观地面对未来。 2. You must confront your problems. 你必须面对自己的问题。 3. It\'s no use to confront your boss. 对抗你的老板是没有用的。 4. A soldier often has to confront danger. 士兵常常要身临险境。', '名词: confronter 过去式: confronted 过去分词: confronted 现在分词: confronting 第三人称单数: confronts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('narrative', '[\'nærətɪv]', 'n.故事；叙述 adj.叙述的；叙述体的', '1. She took up the narrative where John had left off. 她接着讲约翰未讲完的故事。 2. His adventure made an interesting narrative. 他的冒险是个有趣的故事。 3. Tatham was lost in wonder at the narrative. 泰瑟姆听了这个故事，惊奇得出了神。 4. Narrative makes up most of the book. 这本书的大部分篇幅都是叙述性的。 5. The lines form a prelude to his long narrative poem. 这几行诗是他那长篇叙事诗的序诗。', '副词: narratively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stride', '[straɪd]', 'n.大步走；一大步；步伐；进步 vt.跨；跨骑 vi.迈大步走；跨过；分腿站立', '1. In a few strides he crossed the room. 他几大步就穿过了房间。 2. I was three strides from the door. 我距离那门有三大步远。 3. In a big stride he came out of the room. 他一个箭步出了房间。 4. The boy walked with a confident manly stride. 这男孩以自信的男人步伐行走。 5. The boy is too young to stride the ditch. 孩子太小跨不过这条沟。 6. China is striding ahead in her economic construction. 中国正在经济建设方面大步前进。', '名词: strider 过去式: strode 过去分词: stridden 现在分词: striding 第三人称单数: strides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remind', '[rɪ\'maɪnd]', 'vt.使想起；提醒', '1. This story reminds me of my childhood. 这个故事让我想起了我的童年。 2. I feel it is absolutely necessary for me to remind him of the meeting today. 我觉得绝对有必要提醒他今天要开会。', '名词: reminder 过去式: reminded 过去分词: reminded 现在分词: reminding 第三人称单数: reminds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('redress', '[rɪ\'dres]', 'n.赔偿；救济；矫正；缓解 v.纠正；补偿；革除；惩罚；<古>报答；恢复', '1. Any man deserves redress if he has been injured unfairly. 任何人若蒙受不公平的损害都应获得赔偿。 2. You must seek redress in the law courts for the damage to your car. 你的车子受到了损坏，你应当通过法律途径要求赔偿。 3. If the statute of limitations has run,the plaintiff is without redress. 如果过了法定诉讼时效，原告将无法得到救济。 4. A fault confessed is half redress. 认错改正一半错。 5. The team has more men than women so we must redress the balance. 这个队男的多女的少,所以我们得纠正平衡一下。', '名词: redresser 过去式: redressed 过去分词: redressed 现在分词: redressing 第三人称单数: redresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ultimatum', '[ˌʌltɪ\'meɪtəm]', 'n.最后通牒', '1. This ultimatum was bound to create a grave crisis. 这一纸最后通牒必然会引起严重危机。 2. They delivered an ultimatum to that country. 他们给那个国家下了一道最后通牒。', '名词复数: ultimatums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incorruptible', '[ˌɪnkə\'rʌptəbl]', 'adj.（道德上）不受腐蚀的（如不受贿）；不可摧毁的', '1. Judges should be incorruptible. 法官应当廉洁。 2. Bribery won\'t work with him. He\'s incorruptible. 贿赂对他不起作用。他为人清廉。 3. Incorruptible, and just officials will surely be supported by the common people. 廉正清明的官吏肯定会受老百姓拥护的。', '副词: incorruptibly 名词: incorruptibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('verify', '[\'verɪfaɪ]', 'vt.核实；证明', '1. He tried in every way to verify this theory. 他想一切办法来验证这个理论。 2. Men were sent out to verify whether it was true. 几个人被派去查清事实。 3. The truth verified the allegations. 事实证明了这些说法。 4. The reader should verify this calculation. 此式可由读者自行证明。', '名词: verifier 过去式: verified 过去分词: verified 现在分词: verifying 第三人称单数: verifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incentive', '[ɪn\'sentɪv]', 'adj.刺激的；鼓励的 n.刺激；鼓励；动机', '1. Haier is operating with the mechanism of Incentive Management. 海尔实行激励管理机制。 2. We should be incentive to further study in this subject. 我们应在这一课题上鼓励进一步研究。 3. To support the family is an incentive for him to work hard. 养家糊口是他努力工作的刺激因素。 4. Incentives differ from country to country and region to region and are always highest in a depressed area. 这些鼓励措施在国与国、地区与地区之间都不尽相同。一般萧条地区提供的鼓励最高。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refer', '[rɪ\'fɜːr]', 'vt.把 ... 提交；把 ... 归因；归类 vi.参考；谈及；咨询', '1. We referred the proposal to the board of directors. 我们把这一建议提交董事会处理。 2. You should refer this matter to the head office for a decision. 你应当把这事提交总部去决定。 3. He referred all his troubles to bad luck. 他将他的一切麻烦都归因于运气不好。 4. Botanists refer this flower to the rose family. 植物学家将这花归入蔷薇科。 5. You can refer to a dictionary if necessary. 如果有必要，你可以参考字典。', '形容词: referable 名词: referral 过去式: referred 过去分词: referred 现在分词: referring 第三人称单数: refers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stale', '[steɪl]', 'adj.不新鲜的；陈腐的；厌倦的 v.变得不新鲜；腐坏；(动物)撒尿 n.(动物的)尿', '1. His hunger makes his stale bread go down. 饥饿使他把这不新鲜的面包吞了下去。 2. He always bought two loaves of stale bread. 他总是要买两个不新鲜的面包。 3. The males think the females have talent for telling stale tales. 男人认为女人有讲陈腐故事的才能。 4. After ten years in the job, she felt stale and needed a change. 在那个岗位干了十年之后，她觉得腻了，需要换换工作。 5. The pleasure I get from playing guitar never stales. 我对吉它一直兴味盎然。', '副词: stalely 比较级: staler 最高级: stalest 名词: staleness 过去式: staled 过去分词: staled 现在分词: staling 第三人称单数: stales');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compete', '[kəm\'piːt]', 'v.竞争；比赛；对抗', '1. Companies must be able to compete in the marketplace. 公司一定要在市场中有竞争力。 2. Several companies are competing for the contract. 几家公司正为争取一项合同而互相竞争。 3. We can compete with the best teams. 我们能与最好的队竞争。 4. He\'s hoping to compete in the London marathon. 他期盼着参加伦敦马拉松比赛。', '过去式: competed 过去分词: competed 现在分词: competing 第三人称单数: competes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slender', '[\'slendər]', 'adj.细长的；苗条的；微薄的；少量的', '1. It was a long, slender stick of vivid yellow. 那是一根鲜黄色的又细又长的粉笔。 2. All girls want to be slender. 所有女孩都希望苗条。 3. She was slender and had long dark hair. 她身材苗条，有一头长长的黑发。 4. The daughter was to have but a slender provision. 女儿只能得到一份菲薄的嫁妆。', '副词: slenderly 比较级: slenderer 最高级: slenderest 名词: slenderness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inherit', '[ɪn\'herɪt]', 'v.继承；遗传', '1. The eldest son will inherit the title. 长子将继承爵位。 2. She inherited a house from her father. 她从她父亲那儿继承了一所房子。 3. The two children both inherit left-handedness from their parents. 这两个孩子都从父母身上遗传了左撇子。', '名词: inheritor 过去式: inherited 过去分词: inherited 现在分词: inheriting 第三人称单数: inherits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('breakdown', '[\'breɪkdaʊn]', 'n.崩溃；故障；衰弱；分类，明细；跺脚曳步舞', '1. His frequent depressions were the prelude to a complete mental breakdown. 他经常抑郁寡欢,后来精神完全崩溃了。 2. The old car rattled along again after a breakdown. 那辆破车在一次故障后又隆隆地行驶在路上了。 3. She suffered a nervous breakdown. 她患神经衰弱。 4. The accountant gave a breakdown of the expenses. 会计交出一份开支明细帐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excursion', '[ɪk\'skɜːrʒn]', 'n.远足；短途旅行；【物】偏移，漂移，偏离；偏差，偏振', '1. The excursion was the high spot of our holiday. 我们那个假日的最大乐趣是远足。 2. We are planning an excursion to the blue mountain. 我们正在计划去蓝山远足。 3. I was roped in for this excursion before I knew it. 我不知不觉被拉来参加了这次远足旅行。 4. We shall make an excursion to Hangzhou this weekend. 这个周末我们将去杭州旅行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prototype', '[\'proʊtətaɪp]', 'n.原型；范例；雏形', '1. The strange mechanical device is the prototype of modern cars. 这个奇怪的机械装置是现代汽车的原型。 2. Designers have built a working prototype of the car. 设计者已经制造了汽车的工作原型。 3. This is the prototype for future school buildings. 这是未来的学校建筑的蓝本。 4. He is the prototype of good breeding. 他是具有良好教养的典范。', '形容词: prototypal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trudge', '[trʌdʒ]', 'v.缓慢或吃力地走 n.长途跋涉', '1. The old man trudged home through the deep snow. 老人踩着积雪，步履艰难地往家走。 2. He trudge three hour in the snow to get back home. 他在雪中跋涉三个钟点才回到家。 3. It was a long trudge up the hill. 那段上山的路很难走。', '名词: trudger 过去式: trudged 过去分词: trudged 现在分词: trudging 第三人称单数: trudges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('buckle', '[\'bʌkl]', 'n.扣子；皮带扣 v.扣住；弯曲；专心做事；屈服', '1. He unfastened the buckles and took off the coat. 他解开扣子，把上衣脱掉。 2. Mary clasped her belt with a silver buckle. 玛莉用银色扣子扣紧她的腰带。 3. He buckled up his belt tightly. 他把裤带扣得紧紧的。 4. The shock buckled the wheel of my bicycle. 这一碰把我自行车的轮子碰歪了', '过去式: buckled 过去分词: buckled 现在分词: buckling 第三人称单数: buckles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alumnus', '[ə\'lʌmnəs]', 'n.男毕业生；男校友', '1. My father is an alumnus of UCLA. 我父亲是加州大学洛山矶分校的毕业生。 2. President Kennedy was an alumnus of Harvard University. 肯尼迪总统是哈佛大学的毕业生。 3. John is one of his alumni in the university. 约翰是他大学时的校友之一。 4. One of my alumni dropped over to me last week. 上周我的一位校友顺道来看了我。', '名词复数: alumni');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dictatorial', '[ˌdɪktə\'tɔːriəl]', 'adj.独裁的；专政的', '1. Under dictatorial rule, the people languished. 在独裁者的统治下，人民毫无生气。 2. The revolution bring about the downfall of the dictatorial regime. 革命推翻了独裁政权。 3. They resent being ruled over by a dictatorial boss. 他们憎恨受一个专横傲慢老板的管制。 4. Scratchy and dictatorial, he began to question her. 他开始咄咄逼人地追问起她来。', '副词: dictatorially 名词: dictatorialness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tentative', '[\'tentətɪv]', 'adj.不确定的；暂时的；试验性质的；犹豫不决的', '1. He still held a tentative relationship with Mary. 他还和玛丽保持着若即若离的关系。 2. Could we make a tentative appointment for Friday? 我们能暂时先约在星期五吗? 3. We\'ve drawn up a tentative program for the next two weeks. 我们制定了一个之后两个星期的试探性计划。 4. Each step he took was slightly tentative. 他每走一步都有些迟疑不决。', '副词: tentatively 名词: tentativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('leisure', '[\'liːʒər]', 'n.闲暇；休闲', '1. Are you at leisure just now? 你现在有空吗？ 2. Life today is compartmentalized into work and leisure. 现今生活分成工作和闲暇两部分。 3. I have no leisure for playing cards. 我没有闲暇玩牌。 4. He\'s a gentleman of large leisure. 他是一个逍遥自在的绅士。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sociable', '[\'soʊʃəbl]', 'adj.好交际的；社交的', '1. Roger is a very sociable person. 罗杰是个非常好交际的人。 2. But they were a sociable family and liked their neighbors, especially the O\'Hara girls. 不过塔尔顿家是个好交际的家庭，喜欢和邻居尤其是奥哈拉家的姑娘拉来往。 3. As a whole they are friendly and sociable people. 作为一个整体，他们是友善而好社交的人。 4. Sociable people, those who like to be with others, like red. 喜欢社交的人，喜欢和他人在于起的人都喜欢红色。', '副词: sociably 名词: sociableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hostile', '[\'hɑːstl]', 'adj.敌对的；怀敌意的', '1. Let\'s hope they will refrain from hostile actions. 希望他们不采取敌对行动。 2. I don\'t like her manner -- she\'s very hostile. 我不喜欢她的态度--待人如仇敌。 3. I don\'t know why she is hostile to me. 我不知道她为什么对我抱有敌意。 4. The new government was hostile to them. 新政府对他们怀有敌意。', '副词: hostilely');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discipline', '[\'dɪsəplɪn]', 'n.纪律；训练；学科 vt.训练；惩罚', '1. She is strict in the matter of discipline. 她对纪律的要求是严格的。 2. It takes years of discipline to become a pianist. 要成为钢琴家需经多年训练。 3. Applied linguistics is a new and independent discipline. 应用语言学是一门新兴的独立学科。 4. It showed that they had been well disciplined. 这表明他们受过良好的训练。', '形容词: disciplinal 名词: discipliner 过去式: disciplined 过去分词: disciplined 现在分词: disciplining 第三人称单数: disciplines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jealous', '[\'dʒeləs]', 'adj.妒忌的；羡慕的；嫉妒的', '1. He was hounded out of his job by jealous rivals. 他受到忌妒他的竞争者的算计而被迫离职。 2. He was said to be jealous of her. 据说是他忌妒她。 3. I was jealous of Mary\'s new bicycle. 我很羡慕玛丽的新自行车。 4. He is jealous of his colleague\'s success. 他嫉妒同事的成功。', '副词: jealously 名词: jealousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pivot', '[\'pɪvət]', 'n.枢；中心；旋转 adj.在枢轴上转动的；关键的 vt.装枢轴于；以 ... 为中心 vi.在枢轴上转动', '1. A grasping device consisting of two arms joined at one end by a pivot or hingelike scissors. 钳，火钳一种用来抓取的工具，由通过枢轴或枢状剪结合于一端的两臂组成 2. Their daughter was the pivot of their lives. 女儿是他们生活的中心。 3. West Africa was the pivot of the cocoa trade. 西非是可可豆贸易的中心。 4. Because her job had been the pivot of her life, retirement was very difficult. 因为她的工作一向是她生命的支柱，所以退休后日子很不好过。 5. The technicians mounted the arms onto the pivot shafts. 技工将雨刷臂安装在枢轴上。 6. The whole discussion pivots on this one point. 整个讨论内容均以此为中心。 7. The technicians mounted the arms onto the pivot shafts. 技工将雨刷臂安装在枢轴上。', '形容词: pivotable 过去式: pivoted 过去分词: pivoted 现在分词: pivoting 第三人称单数: pivots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('budget', '[\'bʌdʒɪt]', 'n.预算 vt.编预算；为 ... 做预算 vi.节省开支 adj.廉价的；不贵的', '1. Congress has approved the new educational budget. 国会通过了新的教育预算。 2. Our budget needs drastic revision. 我们的预算需作重大修改。 3. The government has budgeted 10000000 pounds for education spending. 政府将10000000英镑编入教育预算。 4. The government plans to budget a new hospital. 政府计划在预算中拨款建一家新医院。 5. If we budget carefully, we\'ll be able to afford a new house. 如果我们精打细算就能买一座新房子了。 6. You can buy high-quality goods at budget prices there. 你可以在那买到物美价廉的商品。', '形容词: budgetary 名词: budgeter 过去式: budgeted 过去分词: budgeted 现在分词: budgeting 第三人称单数: budgets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('faculty', '[\'fæklti]', 'n.（大学的）系或院；全体教员；才能；能力', '1. He is the dean of the Faculty of Medicine. 他是医学院院长。 2. We haven\'t set up the Faculty of Law in our university. 我们学校还没下设法学院。 3. Both faculty and students oppose the measures. 全体教师和学生都反对这种方法。 4. She has the faculty to learn languages easily. 她有轻而易举学会语言的才能。', '名词复数: faculties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enterprise', '[\'entərpraɪz]', 'n.企业；事业；进取心；谋划', '1. This enterprise is now on a firm footing and should soon get profits. 现在这家企业基础稳固，很快就会赢利。 2. They are involved in an exciting scientific enterprise. 他们投身于一项激动人心的科学事业。 3. We need a spirit of enterprise if we are to overcome our difficulties. 如果我们要克服困难，我们就要有进取精神。 4. His latest business enterprise has attracted a lot of attention. 他最新的企业规划引来了很多关注。', '名词: enterpriser');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('individual', '[ˌɪndɪ\'vɪdʒuəl]', 'adj.单独的；一个人的；独有的 n.个人；个体', '1. A teacher can\'t give individual attention to each pupil if his class is large. 如果班上的人数多，老师就不能给予个别辅导了。 2. It is difficult for a teacher to give individual attention to children in a large class. 教师在人数多的班上，很难对各个学生都照顾到。 3. She has her own individual style of doing things. 她有自己独特的行事风格。 4. No individual shall overtop the law. 任何个人的权力都不能凌驾于法律之上。', '副词: individually');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enhance', '[ɪn\'hæns]', 'vt.提高；增加；加强', '1. He made many efforts to enhance his reputation. 他做了许多努力来提高他的声誉。 2. Martial education is an important means to exercise volition and enhance national defense notion. 提出军事教育是锻炼意志,提高国防观念的重要手段。 3. This year, we will review the functions and other aspects of District Councils and enhance our support for them. 今年将展开对区议会功能等方面的检讨,增加对区议会的支持。 4. The programme aims to enhance the employment of young people with disabilities or early signs of mental illness. 计划的目的,是加强残疾或出现精神病早期徵状的青少年的就业能力。', '形容词: enhancive 名词: enhancement 过去式: enhanced 过去分词: enhanced 现在分词: enhancing 第三人称单数: enhances');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cargo', '[\'kɑːrɡoʊ]', 'n.货物；船货', '1. The ship is discharging the cargo. 船正在卸货。 2. Cargo insurance is a major item of our business. 货物保险是我公司的一大项目。 3. The cargo was seriously damaged by water. 船货被水严重损坏。 4. This port handles 100 million tons of cargo each year. 这个港口每年货物吞吐量达1亿吨。', '名词复数: cargoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('naval', '[\'neɪvl]', 'adj.海军的；军舰的', '1. It was unable to turn around at the West end of Chambers Field at the Norfolk Naval Station. 它是不能在诺福克海军的车站室领域的西繁华区回过头的。 2. Or you hear about a naval vessel that\'s up for auction or a vessel that\'s been confiscated by the Customs for smuggling. 或许你会听说有一条海军的船要拍卖，或是有一条让海关没收的走私船。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('charity', '[\'tʃærəti]', 'n.慈善；宽厚；慈善机关(团体)；仁慈', '1. They did so under the mask of charity. 他们是打着慈善的幌子这么做的。 2. True charity doesn\'t consist in almsgiving. 真正的慈善不在于施舍。 3. She was always very generous in her charity. 她行善时总是很慷慨。 4. She regards his moral faults with charity. 她宽恕他的品行不端。', '名词复数: charities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('credulous', '[\'kredʒələs]', 'adj.轻信的；易受骗的', '1. We are less credulous than we used to be. 我们不再像以往那样轻易相信别人了。 2. He always cheats credulous people. 他总是欺骗容易上当的人。 3. John is so credulous that he wil believe what you tell him. 约翰很容易受骗，所有你说的，他都会相信。', '副词: credulously 名词: credulousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('envoy', '[\'envɔɪ]', 'n.外交使节；特使', '1. Our envoy was accredited to the new government. 我国已向该国新政府派遣了外交使节。 2. She is a famous diplomatic envoy. 她是世界著名外交使节。 3. A special peace envoy was sent to the area. 一个和平特使奉命到了这一地区。 4. U.N. envoy Eide acknowledges there have been problems. 联合国特使艾德承认问题的存在。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commend', '[kə\'mend]', 'v.推荐；称赞；嘉奖；把 ... 托付给', '1. I should like to commend this method to you. 我想向您推荐这一方法。 2. I\'d like to commend him to my friends. 我愿意把他推荐给我的朋友们。 3. He commend them for their enthusiasm. 他称赞他们的热情。 4. The guests commend him upon his good manners 客人们称赞他有礼貌。', '形容词: commendable 副词: commendably 名词: commendableness 过去式: commended 过去分词: commended 现在分词: commending 第三人称单数: commends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obscene', '[əb\'siːn]', 'adj.淫秽的；猥亵的', '1. No nudity or obscene lyrics in your music are to be used during your routine. 请勿在上台比赛的音乐中加入猥亵或淫秽的曲调或歌词。 2. Something, such as language or printed matter, considered obscene , prurient, or immoral. 这本书中有很多淫秽的语言。 3. He was taking part in some obscene feast. 他是在参加一个卑鄙猥亵的餐会。 4. The protesters shouted some obscene remarks at the police officers. 抗议者们朝警官们叫喊着一些猥亵的话语。', '副词: obscenely');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agonize', '[\'æɡənaɪz]', 'v.(使)极度痛苦 =agonise(英).', '1. All the time they agonize and pray. 他们一直在忍受苦痛并且祈祷。 2. We agonized for hours about which wallpaper to buy. 对于买哪种壁纸,我们伤了几小时的脑筋。 3. There\'s no reason to agonize over telling people you\'re job hunting. 没有理由为告诉他人你正在找工作而感到苦恼。 4. Do not agonize about falling asleep. The stress will only prevent sleep. 不要为睡不着觉而烦恼，这种压力只会让你更难入睡。', '副词: agonizingly 过去式: agonized 过去分词: agonized 现在分词: agonizing 第三人称单数: agonizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incongruous', '[ɪn\'kɑːŋɡruəs]', 'adj.不协调的；不一致的；前后不一的', '1. I found the scene somewhat incongruous. 我发觉布景有点不协调。 2. A joke that was incongruous with polite conversation. 一个与礼貌谈话不相协调的玩笑。 3. Their acts are incongruous with their principles. 他们的行为与信奉的原则不一致。 4. Negotiating with terrorists is incongruous with national policy. 和恐怖分子进行谈判不符合国家政策。', '副词: incongruously 名词: incongruousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('silt', '[sɪlt]', 'n.淤泥 v.(使)淤塞', '1. The harbor is being up with silt. 那海港被淤泥阻塞了。 2. A concrete wall is built to stop silt from leaking to the conservation land. 一道水泥墙修筑起来，用以防止泥沙流进保留地。 3. The sand have silt up the mouth of the river. 泥沙已把河口堵住了。', '形容词: silty 名词: siltation 过去式: silted 过去分词: silted 现在分词: silting 第三人称单数: silts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oration', '[ɔː\'reɪʃn]', 'n.演说；致辞；叙述法', '1. He was asked to deliver an oration at the meeting. 他被邀请在会议上发表演说。 2. He was asked to give a funeral oration. 他被要求在葬礼上宣读悼词。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sovereignty', '[\'sɑːvrənti]', 'n.主权；独立国', '1. The sovereignty of these islands is in dispute. 这些岛屿的主权有争执。 2. China\'s sovereignty and territorial integrity brook no division. 中国的主权和领土完整不容分割。 3. The issue of sovereignty is a red line that cannot be crossed. 主权问题是一条不能跨越的红线。 4. The declaration proclaimed the full sovereignty of the republic. 这份宣言宣告这个共和国完全独立自主。', '名词复数: sovereignties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pipe', '[paɪp]', 'n.管子；烟斗；管乐器 vt.以管输送；装管道；吹奏；尖声说；(为衣服等)滚边 vi.吹奏管乐；尖叫', '1. Water is spouting out of the pipe. 水正从管子里喷出来。 2. The workers are laying pipes under the road. 工人们正在道路下面铺设管道。 3. The plumber went down to the cellar to fix the leaky pipe. 管道工到地下室去修漏水的管子。 4. He rammed the tobacco into his pipe. 他把烟丝塞进烟斗。 5. The people in the village used to pipe water . 这个村子里的人过去常以管道输送水。 6. He would pipe away on his flute all day and night. 他可以整天整夜地吹奏长笛。', '过去式: piped 过去分词: piped 现在分词: piping 第三人称单数: pipes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remove', '[rɪ\'muːv]', 'v.消除；脱掉；免除；搬迁', '1. He removed the mud from his shoes. 他去掉鞋上的泥。 2. How can we remove the husk of the grains? 我们怎样去掉谷物的外皮？ 3. Come and remove your wet coat. 过来把你的湿上衣脱掉。 4. She asked me to remove my shnes. 她让我把鞋脱掉。', '名词: remover 过去式: removed 过去分词: removed 现在分词: removing 第三人称单数: removes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fertile', '[\'fɜːrtl]', 'adj.肥沃的；富饶的；能繁殖的；多产的；（创造力）丰富的', '1. There are fertile fields in the Nile Delta. 尼罗河三角洲土地肥沃。 2. We have irrigated the desert area to make it fertile. 我们已经灌溉了荒芜地区使它肥沃。 3. It was a pleasant fertile spot, well wooded and rich in pasture. 那是一个富饶的，使人愉快的地方，材木苍然，牧草丰富。 4. This fertile land bears the hopes of the farmers. 这块富饶的土地,孕育着庄稼人的希望！', '副词: fertilely 名词: fertileness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intercept', '[ˌɪntər\'sept]', 'n.截取；妨碍；截距 vt.拦截；阻止', '1. You are a warrior without intercept in that scenario. 此时你就是一个没有拦截的战士了。 2. I don\'t,and I don\'t think you will either after you hear this next intercept. 如果听了以下的截获内容，我相信你不会在怀疑了。 3. Now, no.6 is running up to intercept. 现在6号正要上前去拦截。 4. It is illegal to intercept a letter or parcel before it is delivered. 在送达之前，中途拦截信件或包裹是非法的。', '形容词: interceptive 过去式: intercepted 过去分词: intercepted 现在分词: intercepting 第三人称单数: intercepts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ecology', '[i\'kɑːlədʒi]', 'n.生态学；生态', '1. Ecology helps us understand complex problems. 生态学帮助我们把握复杂问题。 2. He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science. 他开始研究生态学,并决心将他的一生献身于这门学科。 3. Fossils allow us to reconstruct ancient ecology. 化石可以让我们知道古时的生态环境。 4. Concern about ecology is a recent development. 对生态的关心是最近才有的事。', '形容词: ecological 副词: ecologically 名词: ecologist 名词复数: ecologies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avow', '[ə\'vaʊ]', 'vt.承认；公开宣称声明', '1. He avowed that he would never return. 他声明他决不回来了。 2. He avowed openly that he was divorced. 他坦白承认自己离了婚。', '形容词: avowable 副词: avowably 名词: avower 过去式: avowed 过去分词: avowed 现在分词: avowing 第三人称单数: avows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boast', '[boʊst]', 'v.自夸；吹牛；以...为荣 n.自夸；引以为荣的事物', '1. Don\'t boast and don\'t be modest. 不要自夸,也不要太谦虚。 2. That\'s nothing to boast about. 那没有什麽值得自吹的。 3. Nobody should boast of his learning. 谁也不应当夸耀自己的学识。 4. He never boasted of his cleverness. 他未曾夸耀过自己的聪明。 5. That brother of yours is full of boasts. 你那个宝贝兄弟满口大话。', '形容词: boastful 副词: boastfully 名词: boaster 过去式: boasted 过去分词: boasted 现在分词: boasting 第三人称单数: boasts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eager', '[\'iːɡər]', 'adj.热切的；渴望的', '1. He is eager for you to meet his friends. 他热切希望你见见他的朋友。 2. Eager fans mobbed the popular singer. 热切的歌迷们团团围住住这位流行歌手 3. The boys listened to my story with eager attention. 男孩们以热切的心情非常注意地倾听我的故事。 4. He was eager to see her. 他渴望见到她。', '副词: eagerly 比较级: eagerer 最高级: eagerest 名词: eagerness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accentuate', '[ək\'sentʃueɪt]', 'v.重读；强调；突出', '1. Accentuate the word “accent”on the first syllable. 在“accent”一词的第一个音节上加重音符号。 2. Mrs Obama\'s speeches rarely accentuate the positive. 奥巴马夫人的演讲很少强调美国积极的一面。 3. The tight jumper only accentuated his fat stomach. 那件紧身套头毛衣反更突出了他那肥胖的肚子。 4. She has beautiful eyes, so we should accentuate them in the makeup. 她眼睛很美丽，我们在化妆时应该突出她的眼睛。', '名词: accentuation 过去式: accentuated 过去分词: accentuated 现在分词: accentuating 第三人称单数: accentuates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constant', '[\'kɑːnstənt]', 'adj.不变的；经常的 n.常数；恒量', '1. In our world nothing seems constant. 在我们这个世界上似乎没有东西是永恒不变的。 2. The birth rate in this city is almost constant. 这城市的出生率几乎是不变的。 3. The machinery requires constant maintenance. 这些机器需要经常保养维修。 4. The constant friction between the young couple finally caused divorce. 小夫妻俩之间经常的冲突终于导致了离婚。 5. The speed of light is an important constant. 光速是一个重要的常数。', '副词: constantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impurity', '[ɪm\'pjʊrəti]', 'n.不纯；杂质', '1. Impurity of the water made it unfit to drink. 因为水质不纯净，所以不能饮用。 2. The impure mixture with impurity is purified. 含杂质的不纯混合物被提纯。 3. There are some impurities in food. 食物中有一些杂质。 4. Workers are removing impurities from silver. 工人们正去除银中的杂质。', '名词复数: impurities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sharply', '[\'ʃɑːrpli]', 'adv.锐利地；严厉地；厉害地；轮廓清晰、线条分明地', '1. Then, the decision made, she looked at him sharply. 然后，她心意已决，目光锐利地看着吉姆。 2. You should not criticize so sharply in his face. 你不应该当面这么严厉地批评他。 3. He was applauded by a summoned conference hall, but the UN Secretary General Ban Ki-moon was sharply critical. 会议厅里多数代表赞成他的观点，而联合国秘书长潘基文却严厉地批评了这种说法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('canyon', '[\'kænjən]', 'n.峡谷', '1. A canyon usually has a river flowing through it. 峡谷常常有河流经过其中。 2. Arizona is famous for the Grand Canyon. 亚利桑那州因科罗拉多大峡谷而著名。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('playwright', '[\'pleɪraɪt]', 'n.剧作家', '1. This playwright is very popular now. 这位剧作家现在很受欢迎。 2. Bernard Show was the best playwright of his time. 萧伯纳是他那个时代最好的剧作家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('taboo', '[tə\'buː]', 'n.禁忌；禁止接近；禁止使用 adj.禁忌的 vt.禁忌', '1. Cannibalism is perhaps the ultimate cultural taboo. 同类相食也许是人类文化的最高禁忌。 2. There\'s a taboo on smoking in this office. 在这个办公室里一向是都不吸烟的。 3. Among Hindus there is a taboo against killing cows. 印度教徒有禁止杀牛的戒律。 4. Any mention of politics is taboo in his house. 在他家里一提政治就犯忌。 5. Sex is no longer the taboo subject it used to be. 现在不再像过去那样把性的问题视为禁区。 6. A man should taboo bad hobbies, and cultivate good habits. 作为男人应该避讳不良嗜好,培养良好的习惯。', '过去式: tabooed/tabued 过去分词: tabooed/tabued 现在分词: tabooing/tabuing 第三人称单数: taboos/tabus');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recycle', '[ˌriː\'saɪkl]', 'vt.再利用；使再循环；再制 vi.循环 n.再循环', '1. We should try to recycle all our waste paper. 我们应该把所有废纸回收再利用。 2. One thing you can\'t recycle is wasted time. 唯一无法回收利用的是你浪费掉的时间。 3. We should recycle the used things. 我们应回收利用旧东西。 4. We must recycle the cardboard boxes. 我们必须循环使用纸盒子。 5. The ecological system can recycle by itself. 生态系统本身就可以循环。 6. Water recycle is a good way to save our resources. 水循环利用是一种很好的节约资源的方法。', '形容词: recyclable 名词: recycler 过去式: recycled 过去分词: recycled 现在分词: recycling 第三人称单数: recycles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hilarious', '[hɪ\'leriəs]', 'adj.欢闹的；愉快的', '1. The party get quite hilarious after they bring more wine. 当他们拿来更多葡萄酒後聚会变得十分热闹起来。 2. Jimmy Durante\'s buffoonery was hilarious. 吉米·杜兰特的滑稽表演令人捧腹。 3. He does a hilarious imitation of Tony Blair. 他模仿托尼布莱尔的滑稽表演令观众捧腹。 4. A former model wrote a hilarious novel based on pillow talk with her many male friends. 一位前模特儿以她同许多男友的枕头谈话为基础写出了一本有趣的小说。', '副词: hilariously 名词: hilariousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ceremony', '[\'serəmoʊni]', 'n.仪式；礼节；典礼', '1. The marriage ceremony took place in the church. 婚礼在教堂举行。 2. They hold a mystic religious ceremony. 他们举行了一个神秘的宗教仪式。 3. There\'s no need for ceremony between friends. 朋友之间不必拘礼. 4. What the old headmaster said at the graduation ceremony dwells in my mind. 老校长在毕业典礼上讲的话一直留在我的脑海里。', '名词复数: ceremonies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tolerant', '[\'tɑːlərənt]', 'adj.宽容的；容忍的', '1. Of all the girls, she is the most tolerant. 在所有的姑娘当中，她是最宽容的。 2. As a man, you should be tolerant and magnanimous. 一个男人家，应该宽容大度些！ 3. A priest must learn to be tolerant and always suffer fools gladly. 一个神父必须学会宽容和永远甘心容忍愚妄的人。 4. He is not very tolerant of criticism. 他不大能容忍批评。', '副词: tolerantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vent', '[vent]', 'n.排气口；火山口；发泄；表达 v.发泄；表达；排放', '1. The steam found a vent through a crack in the pipe. 蒸气从管子的裂缝漏出去。 2. The vent is not big enough to get the smoke out. 通风孔太小,不能让烟排出去。 3. The explosion cracks the earth\'s surface and scatters ash and huge chunks of rock for many kilometers around the vent. 这样的爆炸把地表炸开以后，其火山灰和巨大石块可散落到火山口周围好几公里远的地方。 4. Foraging crabs and hungry fish feed on bacteria from giant tube worms near a deep sea vent in the Pacific Ocean. 在太平洋里的一座深海火山口附近，饥肠辘辘的螃蟹和鱼类正享用着来自巨型管虫的细菌。 5. I look down on man who vents his anger on his family after having a bad day at work. 我瞧不起那些工作不顺心就拿家里人出气的男人。', '名词: venter 过去式: vented 过去分词: vented 现在分词: venting 第三人称单数: vents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('knowledgeable', '[\'nɑːlɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.博学的，有见识的', '1. They talk to business experts, lawyers and other knowledgeable people. 他们与商务专家、律师和其它博识的人交流。 2. Probably not one knowledgeable Christian will contend that the fullness of that promise has been realized today. 或许没有一个有见识的基督徒会认为所应许的已经在今天实现了。', '副词: knowledgeably 名词: knowledgeability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manipulate', '[mə\'nɪpjuleɪt]', 'vt.操纵；操作；控制；利用；(巧妙地)处理；篡改', '1. A clever politician know how to manipulate public opinion. 聪明的政客知道如何操纵公众舆论。 2. He is one of those who manipulate the market. 他是操纵市场者之一。 3. Do you know how to manipulate a computer ? 你知道怎样操作计算机吗? 4. She uses her charm to manipulate people. 她利用其魅力左右他人。', '形容词: manipulatable 副词: manipulatively 名词: manipulability 过去式: manipulated 过去分词: manipulated 现在分词: manipulating 第三人称单数: manipulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impressively', '[ɪm\'presɪvli]', 'adv.令人难忘地；令人印象深刻地', '1. The admonitions seem to work, for the streets are impressively clean. 警告似乎起了作用，因为大街上令人难忘地干净。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suffuse', '[sə\'fjuːz]', 'v.遍布 ...；弥漫；充满', '1. The evening sky was suffused with crimson. 黄昏时分天空红霞灿灿。 2. A blush suffused his cheeks. 他瞬间满脸通红。 3. They want to move everyone with their behaviors and suffuse the world with love. 她们表示要用自己的行为去感染世界上的每一个人，让爱心充满全世界。', '形容词: suffusive 名词: suffusion 过去式: suffused 过去分词: suffused 现在分词: suffusing 第三人称单数: suffuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abound', '[ə\'baʊnd]', 'v.富于；充满', '1. Most of her poems abound in imagery. 她的诗歌大多数富于形象。 2. The myths and traditions of India abound with references. 印度神话和传统充满了参考价值。 3. A very different world will abound as this comes to be so. 一个非常不同的世界将充满着这一切，当这实现。', '过去式: abounded 过去分词: abounded 现在分词: abounding 第三人称单数: abounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lush', '[lʌʃ]', 'adj.苍翠繁茂的；茂盛的；丰富的 n.酒；酒鬼 v.喝酒', '1. Trains pass through the lush countryside. 火车通过苍翠繁茂的乡下。 2. Ireland is famous for its lush green hills. 爱尔兰以其苍翠的绿色山丘而闻名。 3. The lush vegetation spoke of a damper climate here. 茂盛的植物说明这里的气候是潮湿的。 4. The hills are covered in lush green vegetation. 这片丘岭草木茂盛，郁郁葱葱。 5. This handcrafted Chardonnay is rich with white peach, spice, tropical fruit and has a lush velvety texture. 而此酒正由人工采收，有白桃，香料，热带水果的香味，如丝柔滑的口感更让人一试难忘。', '副词: lushly 比较级: lusher 最高级: lushest 名词: lushness 过去式: lushed 过去分词: lushed 现在分词: lushing 第三人称单数: lushes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evasive', '[ɪ\'veɪsɪv]', 'adj.逃避的；难以捉摸的；闪烁其词的', '1. Stephen didn\'t want to see his sister, so he quickly took evasive action and hid under the bed. 斯蒂芬不愿见他的姐姐，便立即采取规避动作，藏到床底下去了。 2. His eyes gleamed with a smart, evasive light. 他那对眼睛闪耀着一种灵活的难以捉摸的光芒。 3. His evasive reply prompted me to ask him another question. 他闪烁其词的回答促使我提出又一个问题。 4. You can tell from his evasive language that he\'s got something to hide. 从他的闪烁其词能看出他分明是在掩饰什么。', '副词: evasively 名词: evasiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enervate', '[\'enərveɪt]', 'adj.无力的；衰弱的 vt.使无力；使衰弱', '1. A hot climate enervate people who be not used to It . 热的气候使不习惯于热的人衰弱无力。 2. Soft living will enervate the leaders, and those under their command will be changed into beasts. 舒适的生命会弱化领导者，在他们命令之下的会变成了兽。 3. Enervate! - Revives someone after being knocked out, or being the recipient of the Stunning Spell (Stupefy! 让某个被麻醉的人苏醒,或者成为晕倒咒的被施咒者。(麻醉! 4. In the second, be a man, and shake off a miserable passion, which will enervate and destroy you. 如是后一种情况，那就振作起精神，设法摆脱那可怜的、必定会耗掉你全部精力的感情。', '形容词: enervative 名词: enervation 过去式: enervated 过去分词: enervated 现在分词: enervating 第三人称单数: enervates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('worthy', '[\'wɜːrði]', 'adj.有价值的；可尊敬的；值得的；配得上的 n.知名人士；杰出人物', '1. This is a worthy English-Chinese dictionary. 这是一本有价值的英汉词典。 2. This book is worthy of reading. 这本书值得一读。 3. No man thinks more highly than I do of the patriotism, as well as abilities, of the very worthy gentlemen who have just addressed the house. 没有人比我对刚刚向议会全体代表发言的可尊敬的先生们的爱国精神和才干更钦佩了。 4. Mr. Foker himself is a worthy man, though not of high extraction or indeed much education. 福克先生本人也是值得尊敬的,尽管他出身不太高贵,受的教育确实也有限。 5. I want you to sell these two and find more worthy replacements. 我需要你卖这些二和发现更多杰出人物替换。', '副词: worthily 比较级: worthier 最高级: worthiest 名词: worthiness 名词复数: worthies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perceptive', '[pər\'septɪv]', 'adj.敏感的；有洞察力的；感知的', '1. It was very perceptive of you to notice that. 你能注意到此事，真够敏锐的。 2. Her books are full of perceptive insights into the humanity. 她的书充满了对人性敏锐的洞察力。 3. He is a truly perceptive critic. 他确是一位很有眼力的批评家。 4. The quality of writing is closely related with the writer\'s perceptive ability. 写作质量的高低与作者感知能力的高低有直接关系。', '副词: perceptively 名词: perceptivity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kiln', '[kɪln]', 'n.窑；炉 v.烧窑；在干燥炉干燥', '1. They are charring wood in a kiln. 他们正在窑内将木头烧成木炭。 2. This is a perfectly preserved ancient kiln. 这是一座保存十分完好的古窑。 3. I thought porcelain kiln must be very big. 我还以为烧瓷的窑炉都很大呢。', '过去式: kilned 过去分词: kilned 现在分词: kilning 第三人称单数: kilns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adaptation', '[ˌædæp\'teɪʃn]', 'n.改编；改编成的作品；适应；【心】（感官）适应，适应性变化', '1. This story lends itself to film adaptation. 这个故事适合改编拍电影。 2. Scotish adaptation was made about a century later. 大约一个世纪之后的出现了一个苏格兰的改编本。 3. I bought my son an adaptation for children of a play by Shakespeare. 我给我儿子买了为儿童改编的莎士比亚剧本。 4. He made a quick adaptation to the new environment. 他很快适应了新的环境。', '形容词: adaptational 副词: adaptationally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diminutive', '[dɪ\'mɪnjətɪv]', 'adj.小的；小型的；变小的 n.小的人（物）；[语]小词缀；昵称', '1. She has diminutive hands for an adult. 作为一个成年人,她的手显得非常小。 2. She bought a diminutive toy for her daughter. 她给女儿买了个小巧可爱的玩具。 3. We thought her diminutive figure could not suffer that work. 我们认为她那小小的身材不能忍受那项工作。 4. The diminutive, white-haired was deeply troubled. 矮个子的白发老人感到非常为难。 5. Maggie is a diminutive of Margaret. 玛吉是玛格丽特的昵称。', '副词: diminutively 名词: diminutiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('habitat', '[\'hæbɪtæt]', 'n.栖息地；产地', '1. The moth\'s habitat is being destroyed and it has nearly died out. 这种蛾子因栖息地正受到破坏，几乎绝种了。 2. The polar bear\'s habitat is the icy waters of the Arctic. 北极熊的栖息地是冰冷的北极海域。 3. I prefer to see animals in their natural habitat, rather than in zoos. 我宁愿观赏居住在自然栖息地里的动物，而不愿看关在动物园里的动物。 4. That country is the habitat of heroin. 那个国家是海洛因的产地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flagellum', '[flə\'dʒeləm]', 'n.[生]鞭毛；鞭状体', '1. The flagellum regularly disrupted from the posterior part of midpiece. 鞭毛外膜松弛与鞭毛脱离等。 2. Others have only one flagellum. 鞭毛的旋转可以推动细菌在水中行进。', '名词复数: flagella');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('backlighting', '[\'bæklaɪtɪŋ]', '逆光', '1. As a result, backlighting when shooting the failure of the regular people can be rest assured that photographic film. 因此，逆光时经常拍摄失败的人物摄影也可放心拍摄。 2. The availability of the whole spectrum of colours opened up new applications, from full-colour video screens to display backlighting. 全色谱的获得开创了从全彩录像屏幕到逆光显示等新的应用领域。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('linguist', '[\'lɪŋɡwɪst]', 'n.语言学家', '1. The linguist is going to give a lecture tomorrow. 那位语言学家明天要做报告。 2. The linguist go to study tribal language in the field. 语言学家们去实地研究部落语言了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reconcile', '[\'rekənsaɪl]', 'v.调和；和解；妥协；一致', '1. I can\'t reconcile the two extreme views. 我无法调和这两种极端的观点。 2. We tried to reconcile her with her family. 我们试图让她和她的家庭和好。 3. We were finally reconciled when he apologized. 他道歉以后我们终于言归于好了. 4. He had to reconcile himself to his fate. 他必须接受自己的命运。', '形容词: reconciliatory 名词: reconcilement 过去式: reconciled 过去分词: reconciled 现在分词: reconciling 第三人称单数: reconciles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manufacture', '[ˌmænju\'fæktʃər]', 'v.（手工）制造；捏造 n.制造；制造业；（复）产品', '1. This firm manufactures cars. 这家公司生产汽车。 2. We manufacture various types of machine tools. 我公司生产各种型号的机床。 3. You will have to manufacture some kind of excuse. 你得找些借口。 4. She manufactured a false story to hide the facts. 她编 造瞎话以掩盖事实。 5. The manufacture of these small components is expensive. 制造这些小部件是非常昂贵的。', '形容词: manufacturable 名词: manufacturing 过去式: manufactured 过去分词: manufactured 现在分词: manufacturing 第三人称单数: manufactures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ooze', '[uːz]', 'v.（使）渗出；泄漏；流露 n.软泥；渗出物', '1. Black oil was oozing out of the engine. 发动机渗出了黑油。 2. Blood was still oozing from the wound. 伤口仍在渗血。 3. The wound was oozing pus. 伤口在流脓. 4. She was simply oozing (with) charm. 她浑身散发着魅力。', '过去式: oozed 过去分词: oozed 现在分词: oozing 第三人称单数: oozes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('doleful', '[\'doʊlfl]', 'adj.悲哀的；寂寞的；阴沉的', '1. His doleful expression told me everything. 他悲哀的表情让我知道了一切。 2. He pauses and gathers himself for a moment before fixing me with doleful eyes. 皮特停顿了，他蹙眉，有着悲伤落寞的眼神。 3. His countenance, as he came on, wore an abstracted and somewhat doleful air. 他走上来的时候，面上有着一种茫然，而且好象阴郁的神气。', '副词: dolefully 名词: dolefulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grope', '[ɡroʊp]', 'v.(暗中)摸索；探索；<口>(调情时)抚摸…身体', '1. I groped for the door handle in the dark. 我在黑暗中摸索着门把手。 2. We groped our way through the dark streets. 我们摸索着走过黑暗的街道。 3. We have to grope for ways to do thing. 我们只能边探索边干。 4. Just friends. I won\'t grope you, I promise. 只是朋友嘛。我不会对你动手动脚的，我保证。', '副词: gropingly 名词: groper 过去式: groped 过去分词: groped 现在分词: groping 第三人称单数: gropes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('process', '[\'prɑˌsɛs]', 'n.工序；过程 v.加工；处理；起诉；列队前进', '1. Building a car is a long process. 制造一辆小汽车有很长的工序。 2. They went over every process again, but without result. 他们把每道工序又检查了一遍，却仍没有结果。 3. Growth and decay are vital processes. 生长和衰亡是生命过程。 4. Brazil began importing soybeans to process at home. 巴西开始进口大豆在国内加工。', '名词复数: processes 过去式: processed 过去分词: processed 现在分词: processing 第三人称单数: processes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concert', '[\'kɑːnsərt]', 'n.音乐会；一致；和谐 vt.协定；协同安排 vi.合作', '1. The concert will be given on Saturday. 音乐会将于星期六举行。 2. It is good to go to a concert for a change. 到音乐会去换换环境比较好。 3. The newspaper gave much publicity to the concert. 报纸对这次音乐会进行了充分报道。 4. They did not act in concert with one another. 他们的行动互不协调。 5. We will get together to concert our differences. 我们将聚集一起协调分歧。 6. He refused to concert with his partners. 他拒绝和他的伙伴们合作。', '过去式: concerted 过去分词: concerted 现在分词: concerting 第三人称单数: concerts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gorilla', '[ɡə\'rɪlə]', 'n.大猩猩；<口>残暴的人', '1. The gorilla had a massive forehead. 猩猩的前额很大。 2. Gorilla is bigger than chimpanzee. 大猩猩比黑猩猩大。 3. The mountain gorilla is on the verge of extinction. 居住在山区的大猩猩已濒临灭绝。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thesis', '[\'θiːsɪs]', 'n.毕业论文；论文；论题；论点；命题', '1. Charles is writing his graduation thesis now. 查尔斯正在写毕业论文。 2. He has already started his thesis. 他已经开始写毕业论文了。 3. He wrote his doctoral thesis on electromagnetism. 他写有关电磁的博士论文。 4. He\'s been pegging away at his thesis for months. 他写论文已经忙了几个月了。', '名词复数: theses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('load', '[loʊd]', 'n.负荷；重担；装载量 v.装载；给(枪)装子弹；[计算机] 装入', '1. A plane can carry only so much load after all. 一架飞机终归只能承载那么多的负荷。 2. The load is too heavy and the supports buckle . 负荷过重，支柱坍下来。 3. She will not shove the heavy load onto others. 她不愿意把重担推给别人。 4. The baker contracted for a load of flour. 面包师订了买一车面粉的合同。 5. We must use mechanical hoisting to load the goods. 我们必须用起重机来装载货物。', '过去式: loaded 过去分词: loaded 现在分词: loading 第三人称单数: loads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rash', '[ræʃ]', 'n.疹子；大量 adj.鲁莽的；轻率的', '1. While you have this rash you are still infectious. 身上还有这种疹子，就仍然有传染性。 2. A rash has appeared on his body. 他身上出现了丘疹。 3. The heat brought him out in a rash. 因气温很高，他浑身长了皮疹。 4. As soon as popular songs were accepted, fans appeared in a rash 流行歌曲一被接受, 追星族就大量涌现。 5. Don\'t do anything rash. 不要鲁莽行事。', '副词: rashly 比较级: rasher 最高级: rashest 名词: rashness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enable', '[ɪ\'neɪbl]', 'vt.使能够；使可能', '1. Listening to music enables us to feel relaxed. 听音乐能使我们放松。 2. A dog\'s ears enable it to hear the least sound. 狗的耳朵使它能听到极细微的声音。 3. This train will enable me to get there in time. 这列火车能使我及时到达那儿。 4. Hobbies may enable you to make many friends. 业余爱好能够使你结识很多朋友.', '名词: enabler 过去式: enabled 过去分词: enabled 现在分词: enabling 第三人称单数: enables');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solidly', '[\'sɑːlɪdli]', 'adv.坚硬地；稳固地', '1. The secretary said that the programme to phase down British air operations in Indo China is solidly based and progressing. 部长说减少英军在印度支那的空中作战计划是有坚实基础的，并在进展中。 2. It rained solidly for three hours. 雨不停地下了三个小时。 3. We are solidly united on this issue. 我们在这个问题上是团结一致的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feat', '[fiːt]', 'n.技艺；功绩；技艺表演', '1. It was quite a feat to move that piano by yourself. 你真有能耐，一个人挪动那架钢琴。 2. I was amazed to see his dangerous feat. 他的危险技艺让我感到惊讶。 3. The skyscraper is a feat of engineering. 那座摩天大楼是一项工程的壮举。 4. The first flight into space was a brilliant feat. 第一次太空飞行是项光辉的伟绩。', '副词: featly 比较级: feater 最高级: featest');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('figurehead', '[\'fɪɡjərhed]', 'n.装饰船头的人像；傀儡领袖', '1. The queen of that country is only a figurehead. 那个国家的女王只是个有名无实的首脑。 2. He is the son of another Maldini, our figurehead. 他是马尔蒂尼家族的儿子，是米兰的另一个代名词。 3. The chairperson was really just a figurehead. 主席只是一位有名无实的首脑。 4. Otherwise Miller would become a dispensable figurehead. 否则米勒就会变成可有可无的傀儡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ultraviolet', '[ˌʌltrə\'vaɪələt]', 'adj.紫外线的 n.紫外线', '1. The ozone layer shields the earth from the sun\'s ultraviolet rays. 臭氧层保护地球不受太阳紫外线的辐射。 2. A suncream provides adequate protection against harmful ultraviolet rays. 使用防晒霜可以保护皮肤不受紫外线的伤害。 3. Ultraviolet rays can penetrate through clouds. 紫外线可以穿透云层。 4. What are infrared and ultraviolet rays? 什么是红外线和紫外线？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remark', '[rɪ\'mɑːrk]', 'n.评论；备注；注意 v.评论；注意到', '1. They made rude remarks about her appearance. 他们对她的外表横加粗暴的评论。 2. The teacher asked the students to make a remark on this page. 老师要求学生在这页备注。 3. Ellen later regretted her remarks about his private affairs. 后来,艾伦后悔的发现没有好好注意他的私事。 4. The editor remarked that article was well written. 编者评论说那篇文章写得很好。', '名词: remarker 过去式: remarked 过去分词: remarked 现在分词: remarking 第三人称单数: remarks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('experienced', '[ɪk\'spɪriənst]', 'adj.有经验的', '1. An experienced mechanic is in charge of the job. 一位有经验的机械师负责这工作。 2. The job calls for an experienced man. 这份工作需要有经验的人。 3. He is less experienced in writing than teaching. 他写作经验没有教学经验丰富。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mechanical', '[mə\'kænɪkl]', 'adj.机械的；力学的；呆板的', '1. The new car had to be withdrawn from the market because of a mechanical defect. 那种新汽车因有机械缺陷只好撤出市场。 2. They were using a mechanical shovel to clear up the streets. 他们用机械铲土机清理街道。 3. The inhomogeneity of the physical and mechanical characteristics can be considered in these models. 在这些模型中考虑了土的物理和力学的非线性特性。 4. Blinking is a mechanical action of the eyelids. 眨眼是眼睑的无意识动作。', '副词: mechanically 名词: mechanicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sneak', '[sniːk]', 'vt.偷偷摸摸做 vi.偷偷地走；偷偷地做 n.鬼鬼祟祟的人；潜行；溜 adj.出其不意的；暗中进行的', '1. He sneaked a chocolate from the box. 他从盒子里偷拿了一块巧克力。 2. I\'ll see if I can sneak him in after dark. 我看天黑后能否让他偷偷地溜进去。 3. I can sneak you out without being noticed. 我能把你偷偷地带出去，别人了现不了。 4. The cat ate the food and sneaked off. 猫吃完食物就偷偷跑了。 5. The sneak who took our lunch spoiled our picnic. 那个鬼鬼祟祟偷走了我们午饭的人，破坏了我们的野餐。 6. This sneak raid was very successful. We took the enemy leader captive. 这次偷袭非常成功，活捉了敌酋。', '过去式: sneaked/snuck 过去分词: sneaked/snuck 现在分词: sneaking 第三人称单数: sneaks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('batter', '[\'bætər]', 'v.猛击；打坏；往后递倾 n.打击手；面糊；斜外墙', '1. Someone is battering at the door. 有人在使劲敲门。 2. A thousand rocket bombs would not batter it down. 一千发火箭弹，也没法将它摧毁。 3. The ship was battered against the rocks. 船被岩石撞坏了。 4. We need a good batter on our team. 我们队需要一个好击球手。', '过去式: battered 过去分词: battered 现在分词: battering 第三人称单数: batters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('canny', '[\'kæni]', 'adj.精明的；谨慎的；节俭的；狡诈的 adv.<苏格兰>仔细地', '1. The canny old lady knew that the book is too expensive. 那精明的老太太知道那本书太贵了。 2. His a canny merchant who knows where his benefit is. 他是一个精明的商人，深知自己的利益所在。 3. Though his tone was respectful, sometimes obsequious, he was also canny. 尽管语气中颇有敬意，有时候甚至逢迎，但他很谨慎。 4. Johnson was plainly a canny individual. 约翰逊显然是个狡猾的人物。', '副词: cannily 比较级: cannier 最高级: canniest 名词: canniness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obsess', '[əb\'ses]', 'v.着迷；困扰', '1. Entrepreneurs must know their competition, but not obsess over it. 企业家必须了解他们所面临的竞争情况，但是也不必过分沉溺于其中。 2. The fear of death obsessed her throughout her old age. 她晚年一直受著死亡恐惧的困扰。 3. For many people, it\'s easy to obsess over minor issues. 很多人被细小的问题所困扰。', '名词: obsessor 过去式: obsessed 过去分词: obsessed 现在分词: obsessing 第三人称单数: obsesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nutrient', '[\'nuːtriənt]', 'adj.营养的；滋养的 n.营养物；营养品', '1. Clay contains available nutrient elements. 粘土会有有用的营养元素。 2. The nutrient in the soil acts as a stimulus to growth/to make the plants grow. 土壤中的养分能促进植物生长。 3. Sulfur is an essential nutrient for plants. 硫是植物的一种重要的营养元素。 4. Books are the nutrient of the whole world. 书藉是全世界的营养品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obligatory', '[ə\'blɪɡətɔːri]', 'adj.强制性的；义务的；必须的', '1. Attendance at school is obligatory. 上学是强制性的。 2. It is an obligatory step that does not arise from revenge, rancour or other lower emotions, but from the rational necessity to make mankind gain insight. 这是一个强制性的步骤，不产生报复，怨恨或其他低的情感，但是从理性的必要性，使人类了解。 3. Attendance at primary school is obligatory. 上小学是义务的。', '副词: obligatorily');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('portrait', '[\'pɔːrtrət]', 'n.肖像；画像；描写', '1. He is a portrait painter. 他是一个肖像画家。 2. The portrait of her mother was her most prized possession. 她母亲的这张肖像是她最珍爱的物品。 3. I unearthed the portrait from the attic. 我从阁楼上搜出这幅画像。 4. In the portrait he is shown lying on a sofa. 在这张画像中画着他躺在沙发上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fatigue', '[fə\'tiːɡ]', 'n.疲劳；疲乏；劳务杂役 v.（使）疲劳 adj.疲劳的', '1. She hoped to sleep off her fatigue. 她希望睡一觉之后会消除疲劳。 2. The aeroplane wing showed signs of metal fatigue. 机翼显出有金属疲劳的现象。 3. He was beaten out with fatigue when he got home. 他回到家里时已是疲惫不堪。 4. Who is on fatigue duty today? 今天谁担任杂役? 5. The patient fatigues easily. 病人容易疲劳。 6. They were shedding their fatigue. 身上疲劳的感觉渐渐都消失了。', '过去式: fatigued 过去分词: fatigued 现在分词: fatiguing 第三人称单数: fatigues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quartz', '[kwɔːrts]', 'n.石英', '1. Quartz crystal is perfectly crystallized. 石英晶体是完美的结晶。 2. Quartz crystals are seldom used in such handsets. 石英晶体是很少使用这种手机。', '形容词: quartzose');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maxim', '[\'mæksɪm]', 'n.格言；箴言；普遍真理 Maxim: 马克西姆(姓氏).', '1. This was a maxim well understood by Turloch. 这是特洛克心领神会的格言。 2. This maxim has been done to death. 这个格言重复得太多了，简直令人发腻。 3. Please lay the maxim to your heart. 请把此格箴言记在心里。 4. Oh, should the maxim be modified a little? 哦，莎翁的这句箴言是不是应当修改？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concentration', '[ˌkɒnsen\'treɪʃən]', 'n.集中；专心；浓度', '1. The tennis players need total concentration during play. 网球运动员在比赛中需要全神贯注。 2. Stress and tiredness often result in a lack of concentration. 紧张和疲劳常使人精神不集中。 3. Concentration is essential if you want to do a good job. 如果你想把事情做好,专心是必要的。 4. His area of concentration is economics. 他专心研究经济学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insistence', '[ɪn\'sɪstəns]', 'n.坚持；强调；坚决主张', '1. On my insistence, he cleaned the room. 经我坚持, 他才打扫了房间。 2. The too early insistence on mastery may discourage students. 过早强调熟练掌握会使学生丧失信心。 3. The men were kept on by the firm at the insistence of the Union. 由于工会的坚决要求,公司继续雇用了那批工人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deputy', '[\'depjuti]', 'n.代表；副手；议员', '1. My younger brother is my deputy during my absence. 我不在时，我弟弟代表我。 2. He is a deputy to the National People\'s Congress. 他是人民代表大会代表。 3. I must find someone to act as a deputy for me during my absence. 我必须找一个人，在我离开期间代理我的职务。 4. I am resigning as chairman and handing over to my deputy. 我现在辞去主席职位，交由我的副手接替。', '名词复数: deputies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('medieval', '[ˌmedi\'iːvl]', 'adj.中世纪的', '1. Knighthood was an ideal in medieval Europe. 在中世纪的欧洲，成为骑士是理想。 2. The medieval town was fortified with a high wall and a deep moat. 这座中世纪的城市周围建有城墙和护城河。 3. This church is a classic example of medieval architecture. 这座教堂是中世纪建筑风格的典型实例。 4. The gallery is a treasure trove of medieval art. 这个画廊是中世纪艺术的宝库。', '副词: medievally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('output', '[\'aʊtpʊt]', 'n.产量；输出功率；输出 vt.输出(信息等)', '1. Output has tripled. 产量已增加到三倍。 2. This country ranks last in industrial output. 这个国家的工业生产排名最後。 3. The average output of the factory is 20 cars a day. 该工厂的平均产量是每天20辆汽车。 4. Have you got the one which has an output of 150 horsepower? 你们有没有输出功率是一百五十（150）马力的? 5. The printer will output colour chart. 打印机将会输出彩色图表。', '过去式: outputted/output 过去分词: outputted/output 现在分词: outputting 第三人称单数: outputs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dissimulate', '[dɪ\'sɪmjuleɪt]', 'v.掩饰；假装；装糊涂', '1. Checked motifs dissimulate their patterns under a layer of black pigments. 格子基调在黑颜料层下掩饰了它们图形。', '形容词: dissimulative 名词: dissimulation 过去式: dissimulated 过去分词: dissimulated 现在分词: dissimulating 第三人称单数: dissimulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proxy', '[\'prɑːksi]', 'n.代理人；代理权；委托书 adj.代理的', '1. You may appoint a proxy to vote for you. 你可以委托他人代你投票。 2. She is acting as proxy for her husband. 她作她丈夫的代表。 3. Icahn is currently organizing a shareholder proxy dispute in an attempt to win control of Yahoo. 目前伊坎正在组织一场股东代理权之争，试图赢得雅虎的控制权。 4. A fair blind proxy blind signature scheme with the property of proxy revocation is proposed. 提出了一个具有可收回代理权特性的公平盲代理盲签名方案。 5. How can I determine my proxy settings? 我怎么知道我的代理服务器的设置?', '名词复数: proxies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expound', '[ɪk\'spaʊnd]', 'v.详细说明；阐述；解释', '1. Laws are a dead letter without courts to expound and define their true meaning and operation. 法律如果没有法院来详细说明和解释其真正意义和作用，就是一纸空文。 2. He has an hour to expound his views to the public. 他有一小时可以向大众阐述他的观点。 3. Secondly, I expound the trend and reason for the administration legislates. 其次，阐述了行政立法的发展趋势及成因。 4. Laws are a dead letter without courts to expound and define their true meaning and operation. 法律如果没有法院来详细说明和解释其真正意义和作用，就是一纸空文。', '名词: expounder 过去式: expounded 过去分词: expounded 现在分词: expounding 第三人称单数: expounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('depreciate', '[dɪ\'priːʃieɪt]', 'v.贬值；降价；轻视', '1. If you neglect this property, it will depreciate. 如果你忽视这份资产，它无形中就贬值了。 2. New cars start to depreciate as soon as they are on the road. 新车一上路就开始贬值。', '名词: depreciator 过去式: depreciated 过去分词: depreciated 现在分词: depreciating 第三人称单数: depreciates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skim', '[skɪm]', 'vt.撇去；略读；掠过；滑过 vi.掠过；表面凝结；<俚>瞒报 n.浮沫；略读；脱脂物', '1. It took me an hour to skim the book. 我花了一小时把这本书浏览了一遍。 2. A seagull skims the water. 海鸥掠过水面。 3. The hovercraft is able to skim over the water. 气垫船能掠过水面飞速行驶。 4. During the cold night, the puddles skimmed over. 夜间寒冷，水洼面上结了冰。 5. I notice you have two quarts of skim milk. 我看到你拿了两夸托脱脂牛奶。', '过去式: skimmed 过去分词: skimmed 现在分词: skimming 第三人称单数: skims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convection', '[kən\'vekʃn]', 'n.(热的)对流', '1. The machine circulated hot air by convection. 这个机器使热空气通过对流来循环。 2. Heat can be delivered by convection, radiation, and thermal conduction. 热气可由对流、辐射和热传导来传递。 3. Convection is the principal agent of heat transfer in the atmosphere and oceans. 对流是大气和海洋中热传输的主要方式。 4. The main parameterof heat convection process is heat transfer coefficient. 反映对流换热过程特性的主要参数是对流换热系数。', '形容词: convectional 副词: convectively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mild', '[maɪld]', 'adj.温和的；柔和的；宽大的；清淡的', '1. He has a mild nature. 他的性格温和。 2. He gave a mild answer, in spite of his anger. 尽管他十分恼火,他还是态度温和地回答了。 3. The coastal area has very mild winter, but by contrast the central plains become extremely cold. 靠近海岸的地区有很温和的冬天,相比而方,靠近中央的平原就变得非常寒冷。 4. The patient has a mild fever. 那个病人有些轻微的发烧。', '副词: mildly 比较级: milder 最高级: mildest 名词: mildness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vocation', '[voʊ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.职业；行业；使命', '1. She chose nursing as her vocation. 她选择护士为职业。 2. He was equipped with knowledge for the vocation. 他具有这项职业的学识。 3. She struggled for years to find her true vocation. 她多年来苦苦寻找真正适合自己的职业。 4. The industry is facing vocation conformity in China. 在中国,这种工业面临行业整合。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('violate', '[\'vaɪəleɪt]', 'v.侵犯；违反；扰乱；亵渎；强奸', '1. Don\'t violate other people\'s copyright. 不要侵犯他人版权。 2. I\'m committed not to violate the rules. 我有义务不违反规定。 3. The country violated the international agreement. 这个国家违反了国际协议。 4. The sound of guns violated the peace of the countryside. 炮声扰乱了乡村的宁静。', '形容词: violative 名词: violator 过去式: violated 过去分词: violated 现在分词: violating 第三人称单数: violates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drowsy', '[\'draʊzi]', 'adj.昏昏欲睡的；令人昏昏欲睡的 adj.寂静的', '1. These tablets will make you drowsy. 这些药片会使你昏昏欲睡。 2. I\'d just woken up and was still drowsy. 我刚醒，还觉得困。 3. The story took place on a drowsy summer afternoon. 这个故事发生在一个令人昏昏欲睡的夏日午后。 4. He thought of home, of drowsy fields and villages bathed by the sun. 他想起了家乡，想起那沐浴在阳光下的静静的田野和村庄。', '副词: drowsily 比较级: drowsier 最高级: drowsiest 名词: drowsiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('explosive', '[ɪk\'sploʊsɪv]', 'adj.爆炸(性)的；引发争论的；大声的 n.炸药', '1. Hydrogen is highly explosive. 氢极易爆炸。 2. The most impressive volcanic phenomena are explosive eruptions. 最令人难忘的火山现象是爆炸喷发。 3. The question of race today is an explosive one. 种族问题在今天是一个会引起激烈争论的问题。 4. He bent double with explosive laughter. 他大笑得直不起腰来。 5. We carefully moved the explosive to another place. 我们谨慎地把炸药转移到了另一个地方。', '副词: explosively 名词: explosiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shaft', '[ʃæft]', 'n.柄；竖井；杆状物；矛；轴；（一道）光线 vt.苛刻地对待；装杆于', '1. In rotating, the shaft splashes oil up into the bearings. 当轴旋转的时候就把油溅入轴承。 2. The air flows down to a shaft and thus loses potential energy. 空气向下进入竖井，因而失去势能。 3. The horse stood between the shafts of the carriage. 马站在大车车辕中间。 4. If you bring them back to the lonely moor, you have to hit the shield three times with the shaft of the spear and then the silence of the moor will be broken forever. 如果你把这矛和盾带回到偏僻的荒野来，你必须要用矛的柄击银盾三下，这样荒野的寂静就能永远被打破。', '过去式: shafted 过去分词: shafted 现在分词: shafting 第三人称单数: shafts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mortal', '[\'mɔːrtl]', 'adj.致命的；终有一死的；不共戴天的；极度的 n.凡人', '1. His injuries proved mortal. 他的伤成了致命伤。 2. He received a mortal wound soon after the battle began. 战争开始后不久, 他就受到了致命的重伤。 3. Man is mortal. 人都是会死的。 4. The antagonisms between the two empires and systems were mortal. 这两个帝国和两种制度之间，有着不共戴天的仇恨。 5. No mortal could vie with Zeus. 任何凡人都没法与宙斯匹敌。', '副词: mortally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('packed', '[pækt]', 'adj.塞满的；收拾好行李的；紧压的 动词pack的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The chaplain came and preached to a packed church. 牧师来给挤满教堂的人们讲道。 2. In a packed and silent courtroom the judge began to sum up. 在挤满人的肃静的法庭上，法官开始对诉讼案件加以扼要评述。 3. Yet he took time out from his packed schedule to receive us. 他非常繁忙，但仍挤出时间来接见我们。 4. I\'m all packed and ready to go. 我已打点好行装，等待出发了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('popular', '[\'pɑːpjələr]', 'adj.受欢迎的；通俗的；流行的；大众的', '1. Her charm of manner made her very popular. 她风度优雅，备受欢迎。 2. Baseball is more popular than any other sport in Japan. 在日本，棒球比其他任何运动都受人欢迎。 3. He is very interested in what are called popular songs. 他对所谓的流行歌曲很感兴趣。 4. Fashion is a very popular magazine in America. 《时尚》是美国很流行的杂志。', '副词: popularly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excitement', '[ɪk\'saɪtmənt]', 'n.激动；兴奋', '1. The excitement quickened my pulse. 激动使我的心跳加快。 2. Her eyes kindled with excitement. 她的眼睛里闪耀出激动的神色。 3. The boys were running in excitement. 男孩们兴奋地跑来跑去。 4. Her heart was throbbing with excitement. 她兴奋得心直跳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cunning', '[\'kʌnɪŋ]', 'adj.狡猾的；有眼光的；精巧的；可爱的 n.【C】狡诈；灵巧', '1. Many politicians are cunning sophists. 许多政客都是狡猾的诡辩家。 2. The fox is known for its cleverness and cunning. 狐狸的机敏和狡猾是人所共知的。 3. She showed her cunning in the way she avoided answering the question. 她对问题避而不答，显示出她很狡猾。 4. He devised a very cunning scheme to help her. 他想出一个帮助她的很好的办法。 5. The fox is believed to have a great deal of cunning. 人们相信狐狸十分狡猾。', '副词: cunningly 名词: cunningness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excavate', '[\'ekskəveɪt]', 'v.挖掘；挖开；发掘（古物）', '1. It took a long time to excavate the ancient city of Troy. 挖掘古老的特洛伊城，花了很长时间。 2. I let him excavate around the mine. 我准许他在金矿周围挖掘。 3. They plan to excavate a large hole. 他们计划挖个大洞。 4. The archaeologists excavated a buried city. 考古学家发掘出一个埋在地下的城市。', '过去式: excavated 过去分词: excavated 现在分词: excavating 第三人称单数: excavates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('current', '[\'kɜːrənt]', 'n.趋势；(水、气、电)流 adj.现在的；流通的', '1. Nothing disturbs the peaceful current of life in the village. 没有任何事干扰村里一向平静的生活. 2. The block becomes magnetic when the current is switched on. 通电时线圈即具磁性。 3. The current is deep and strong down the stream. 下游的水又深又急。 4. The current trend is towards informal clothing. 目前的趋势是穿着比较随便。', '副词: currently 名词: currentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('male', '[meɪl]', 'adj.男性的；雄性的 n.男子；雄性动物', '1. The male voice is deeper than the female. 男性的嗓音比女性的低沉。 2. We need some male subjects for a psychology experiment. 我们需要几个男子作心理学实验对象。 3. In early days only male athletes were allowed to take part in the Olympic Games. 在奥林匹克运动会早期，只有男性运动员才能参加比赛。 4. This flower is a male flower. 这朵花是雄花。 5. The male is physically stronger than the female. 男性在身体上要比女性强壮。', '名词: maleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vault', '[vɔːlt]', 'n.窖；穹；地下室；撑竿跳 vt.做成圆拱形；撑竿跳跃 vi.跳跃', '1. He was buried in the family vault. 他被安葬在家庭的墓穴里。 2. In medieval times, poets often called the sky \"the vault of heaven\". 在中世纪时期，诗人常把天空叫作“苍穹”。 3. She put her jewels in a vault at the bank. 她将珠宝放在银行的金库里。 4. This underground vault is theftproof. 这所地下保管库是防盗的。 5. I don\'t think I can vault over. The wall is so high. 我想我跳不过去，这墙太高。', '名词: vaulter 过去式: vaulted 过去分词: vaulted 现在分词: vaulting 第三人称单数: vaults');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indifferent', '[ɪn\'dɪfrənt]', 'adj.漠不关心的；无关紧要的；平凡的；中立的', '1. He is indifferent to the result of the exam. 他对考试结果漠不关心。 2. She seems indifferent, but deep down she\'s very pleased. 她貌似无动於衷，其实心里非常高兴。 3. Many one or little one is indifferent to me. 多一个或少一个对我是无关紧要的。 4. It was utterly indifferent to her who he was. 封她来说，他是谁，根本是无关紧要的事。', '副词: indifferently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('engaging', '[ɪn\'ɡeɪdʒɪŋ]', 'adj.动人的；迷人的；有魅力的 动词engage的现在分词.', '1. Her kindness, recommended by so pretty a face, was engaging. 她那可爱的脸蛋上浮泛的善意是动人的。 2. A person engaging in the activity of programming is referred to as a programmer. 动人的在规画的活动中的一个人被称为一个程序师。 3. Many people were attracted by her engaging smile. 许多人被她迷人的微笑所吸引了。 4. They are engaging in a duel of words. 他们双方在斗嘴。', '副词: engagingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emend', '[i\'mend]', 'vt.修订；校订', '1. Many men are needed to emend this book. 修订这本书需要许多人手。', '名词: emender 过去式: emended 过去分词: emended 现在分词: emending 第三人称单数: emends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wheedle', '[\'wiːdl]', 'v.(以甜言蜜语)诱惑；(用甜言蜜语)哄骗', '1. She managed to wheedle an extra day\'s pay out of him. 她花言巧语地骗他多付了一天钱。 2. The children wheedled me into letting them go to the film. 孩子们把我哄得同意让他们去看电影了。', '副词: wheedlingly 名词: wheedler 过去式: wheedled 过去分词: wheedled 现在分词: wheedling 第三人称单数: wheedles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prestigious', '[pre\'stɪdʒəs]', 'adj.享有声望的；声望很高的；<古>魔术的', '1. Her first novel won a prestigious literary prize. 她的第一部小说就获得了一个颇具声望的文学奖。 2. After all,she\'s the most prestigious wedding planner in San Francisco. 她毕竟是旧金山最负盛名的婚礼策划人。 3. He is prestigious professor in this field. 他是这个领域里有声望的教授。 4. He is a prestigious figure in his village and what he says carries a lot of weight. 他在村里是个有头有脸的，说话很有分量。', '副词: prestigiously 名词: prestigiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aspersion', '[ə\'spɜːʒən]', 'n.洒(尤指洒圣水)；诽谤；中伤', '1. We cast no aspersion on the man or his program.Mr.Obama, in his short career, has not strongly associated himself with any policy idea. 我们无意诽谤这个人或他的计划，然而奥巴马先生在他短暂的职业生涯里，从未对任何政策主张表现过强烈支持的态度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('negligent', '[\'neɡlɪdʒənt]', 'adj.疏忽的；粗心的；不在意的', '1. The intentional or negligent act of the defendant that directly interferes with the plaintiff\'s exclusive possession of land without lawful justification. 任何人只要有意图或者是疏忽的侵入他人的土地，同时在没有对方的意识或者许可之下，直接的影响他人享用自己土地就称之为侵入土地。', '副词: negligently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('respiration', '[ˌrespə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.呼吸；【生】一次呼吸，呼吸量；植物呼吸作用', '1. He was using his accessory muscles of respiration. 他在用呼吸辅助肌进行呼吸。 2. Respiration is difficult at great heights. 在很高的高原上呼吸很困难。', '形容词: respirational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pulse', '[pʌls]', 'n.脉搏；脉冲；[植]豆类 v.搏动；跳动', '1. His pulse is not very regular. 他的脉搏不很规则。 2. The excitement quickened my pulse. 激动使我的心跳加快。 3. I could feel a fluttering pulse. 我感到脉搏跳动。 4. The machine emits sound pulses. 这台机器可发出声脉冲信号。 5. I could feel blood pulsing through my veins. 我感到浑身血液在沸腾。', '过去式: pulsed 过去分词: pulsed 现在分词: pulsing 第三人称单数: pulses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annul', '[ə\'nʌl]', 'v.废除；消减；取消；宣告无效', '1. The effect of the statute was to annul this covenant. 但州法规废除了这一契约。 2. Annul the previously transmitted clearance. 取消先前发给的许可。 3. For them, the decision to annul same-sex marriages will be personal, even painful. 对这些同性恋者来说，决定取消婚礼会是私人的，而且是痛苦的。', '过去式: annulled 过去分词: annulled 现在分词: annulling 第三人称单数: annuls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deport', '[dɪ\'pɔːrt]', 'vt.驱逐出境；持...举止', '1. Even if they didn\'t put her in jail, they would deport her. 即使他们不把她关入监狱,他们也会把她驱逐出境。 2. We deport aliens who slip across our borders. 我们把偷渡入境的外国人驱逐出境。 3. It’s important to teach a child how to deport himself in public. 教会小孩在公众场合如何举止得体十分重要。', '过去式: deported 过去分词: deported 现在分词: deporting 第三人称单数: deports');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solitude', '[\'sɑːlətuːd]', 'n.孤独；独居；荒僻之地；幽静的地方', '1. I am not fond of solitude. 我不喜欢孤独。 2. He passed twenty-four years in solitude. 他在孤独中度过了二十四年。 3. I was sociable enough, but I enjoyed solitude too. 我很善于交往，但我也喜欢独居的生活。 4. A person who withdraws from the world to live in seclusion and often in solitude. 隐士逃遁离开这个世界而居住于偏僻之地且常常是独处的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('radiant', '[\'reɪdiənt]', 'adj.发光的；明亮的；辐射的', '1. As you evolve, the petals unfold to reveal a radiant jewel in the center. 当你进化的时候，花瓣绽开显现出中心发光的珠宝。 2. Giant, snow-white in colour and gleaming bright, will beget a radiant people. 一位巨人，雪白的肤色，闪烁着明亮的光，会产生发光的人。 3. Giant, snow-white in colour and gleaming bright, will beget a radiant people. 一位巨人，雪白的肤色，闪烁着明亮的光，会产生发光的人。 4. Quantum theory proposes that radiant energy is transmitted in discrete units. 量子理论的提出辐射的能量能传递离散的单位。', '副词: radiantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hardware', '[\'hɑːrdwer]', 'n.五金器具；[计] 硬件；武器装备', '1. They carried a vast inventory of hardware. 他们带着大量的五金器具存货。 2. My house stands cheek by jowl with a hardware shop. 我家紧靠一家五金商店。 3. I know nothing about computer hardware. 我对计算机硬件一窍不通。 4. We deal in hardware but not software. 我们只经营硬件而不经营软件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('placate', '[\'pleɪkeɪt]', 'v.抚慰；平息；和解', '1. His intent is clearly not to placate his critics. 他的目的显然不是要安抚批评他的人。 2. The concessions did little to placate the students. 让步根本未能平息学生的愤怒。', '形容词: placatory 名词: placater 过去式: placated 过去分词: placated 现在分词: placating 第三人称单数: placates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apprehension', '[ˌæprɪ\'henʃn]', 'n.理解；忧惧；逮捕；了解', '1. The matter is beyond my apprehension. 这件事我无法理解。 2. He felt some apprehension over the result. 他对结果有点担心。 3. He looked around the room with apprehension. 他恐惧地检查房间的四周。 4. The thief, after his apprehension, escaped. 这贼被捕后又逃了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dominion', '[də\'mɪniən]', 'n.统治；主权；领土 Domimion：. n.英联邦的自治领土', '1. Alexander held dominion over a vast area. 亚历山大曾统治过辽阔的地域。 2. The colonists were finally freed from the dominion of the oppressors. 殖民地人民终于摆脱了压迫者的统治。 3. It is a stupid and barbarous way to extend dominion by arms. 武力不过是主权扩张的一种愚蠢而野蛮的方式。 4. European powers no longer rule over great overseas dominions. 欧洲列强不再统治大块海外领土了。 5. The Irish Free State came into being as a British dominion in 1922. 1922年,爱尔兰自由国家成为不列颠的一个自治领。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('urgent', '[\'ɜːrdʒənt]', 'adj.紧急的；急迫的；坚持要求的', '1. They\'ve made an urgent request for international aid. 他们紧急请求国际援助。 2. I was prevented from going by urgent business. 我因急事不能去。 3. Jean spoke, her voice low and urgent. 吉恩说话的时候声音压得很低,感觉很急迫。 4. Seeing that no one takes actions, he spoke to me in an urgent whisper. 没看到一个人采取行动,他忍不住向我低声催促。', '副词: urgently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bigoted', '[\'bɪɡətɪd]', 'adj.固执己见的；心胸狭窄的 动词bigote的过去式和过去分词.', '1. She\'s so bigoted that she refuses to accept anyone who doesn\'t think like her. 她是如此固执己见，绝不接受任何不喜欢她的人。 2. He was bigoted and racist. 他心胸狭窄，是个种族主义者。', '副词: bigotedly 名词: bigotedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stipulate', '[\'stɪpjuleɪt]', 'v.规定；保证 adj.有明文规定的', '1. The Constitution stipulate that women shall have equal rights with men in voting and being elected. 宪法规定妇女和男子一样，有同等的选举权和被选举权。 2. We stipulate that our salesgirl must be polite to customers . 我们规定售货小姐们必须礼貌待客。 3. Can you stipulate they would carry out the treaty? 你能保证他们会执行该条约吗? 4. The company fails to pay on the date stipulate in the contract. 该公司没有按合同中规定的日期付款。', '名词: stipulator 过去式: stipulated 过去分词: stipulated 现在分词: stipulating 第三人称单数: stipulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('soothe', '[suːð]', 'v.缓和；使安静；安慰', '1. He smeared some balm on his hand to soothe the pain. 他在手上涂了些药膏来止痛。 2. He tried to soothe the crying child. 他试着去哄那个在哭的孩子。 3. The soft texture of the blanket can soothe her. 这条毯子柔软的触感可以让她安静下来。 4. A nice cup of tea will soothe your nerves. 一杯好茶可以使你的心绪平静下来。', '名词: soother 过去式: soothed 过去分词: soothed 现在分词: soothing 第三人称单数: soothes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('charter', '[\'tʃɑːrtər]', 'n.宪章；特许；(船、机、车等的)租赁 vt.包租；特许；发给 ... 执照 adj.特许的', '1. You should read the Charter of the United Nations. 你应该阅读一下联合国宪章。 2. The rights of our citizens are governed by charter. 我们公民的权利是由宪章规定的。 3. The company was granted a charter trade in the occupied territory. 这家公司被授予特权，可以在被占领地区进行贸易活动。 4. The holiday-makers chartered a boat to go fishing. 渡假者租了一艘船去钓鱼。', '名词: charterer 过去式: chartered 过去分词: chartered 现在分词: chartering 第三人称单数: charters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('humanity', '[hjuː\'mænəti]', 'n.人类；人性；人道；慈爱；(复)人文学科', '1. Such a man is a stain to humanity. 这种人是人类的耻辱。 2. How can you turn aside from suffering humanity? 面对受苦受难的人类，你怎么能毫无同情心呢？ 3. Humanity is a mixture of good and bad qualities. 人性是善与恶的混合体. 4. He treated the prisoners with humanity. 他人道地对待俘虏。', '名词复数: humanities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wick', '[wɪk]', 'n.蜡烛芯；灯芯', '1. It was empty, but a feeble tallow candle, with a broken back and a long, cauliflower-headed wick sputtered upon the table. 房间是空空洞洞的，只点了一支暗淡无光的牛脂蜡烛，背部开裂，蜡烛芯长长的，花椰菜头似的，蜡烛油溅泼在桌子上。 2. A wick connects it to a reservoir. 一灯芯绳把它与水槽相连。 3. The wick is the quintessence of the candle. 灯芯是蜡烛的精华。', '过去式: wicked 过去分词: wicked 现在分词: wicking 第三人称单数: wicks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('counsel', '[\'kaʊnsl]', 'n.劝告；建议；诉讼律师 v.提供建议；劝告', '1. Good counsel has no price. [谚]忠言无价。 2. Listen to the counsel of your elders. 听从长辈的劝告吧. 3. Each side of a case in court has its own counsel. 法庭上原告和被告双方都有各自的律师。 4. The court heard counsel for both sides. 法庭听取了双方律师的陈述. 5. Most experts counsel caution in such cases. 大多数专家建议在这样的情况下要谨慎从事。', '过去式: counseled/counselled 过去分词: counseled/counselled 现在分词: counseling/counselling 第三人称单数: counsels/counsels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('career', '[kə\'rɪr]', 'n.生涯；职业；事业 vi.猛冲；飞跑', '1. His early career was not a great success. 他早期的生涯并不很成功。 2. She is a career woman rather than a housewife. 她是职业妇女而不是家庭主妇。 3. Young as I am,I already know what career I want to follow. 我虽然还小,可是对要从事的职业已胸有成竹了。 4. His career took off in 1997. 1997年他的事业开始有了起色。 5. He careered down the road on a bicycle. 他骑着自行车沿路飞奔而去。', '过去式: careered 过去分词: careered 现在分词: careering 第三人称单数: careers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('luxuriant', '[lʌɡ\'ʒʊriənt]', 'adj.繁茂的；丰富的；肥沃的；华丽的；奢华的', '1. Luxuriant forests covered the hills. 山上长满茂密的树林。 2. The bees are humming over the luxuriant flowers. 蜜蜂在繁茂的花丛上嗡嗡作响。 3. The backyard of our house has a luxuriant growth of weeds. 我们家的后院长了一大堆杂草。 4. Farming was easy in this luxuriant soil. 在这片沃土上耕种是件易事。', '副词: luxuriantly 名词: luxuriance');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('due', '[duː]', 'adj.应有的；到期的；预定的；应付的 n.应得物；会费', '1. When it comes to giving due respect to the old people, she feels a bit uneasy. 说到给老人应有的尊敬,她有些不自在。 2. The BBC must ensure that due impartiality is preserved in its news programmes. 英国广播公司必须确保新闻节目保持应有的公正。 3. If you\'re going to the library, would you mind returning this book for me? It\'s due today. 如果你要去图书馆的话,是否介意替我还一下这本书呢?它今天到期。 4. The English version of the novel is due for publication next year. 这部小说的英文译本预定明年出版发行。 5. He received a large reward, which was no more than his due. 他得到了一大笔奖金,这只是他应得的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consume', '[kən\'suːm]', 'v.消耗；吃喝；毁灭', '1. His old car consumed much gasoline. 他的旧汽车耗油很多。 2. Each year Americans consume a high percentage of the world\'s energy. 每年美国人都消耗掉世界能源的很大比例 3. I\'m sure that Chinese people consume the largest amount of rice in the world. 我敢肯定,世界上中国人吃掉的大米最多。 4. I saw the flames consuming the whole building. 我看见火焰吞噬了整栋建筑物。', '过去式: consumed 过去分词: consumed 现在分词: consuming 第三人称单数: consumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('microbe', '[\'maɪkroʊb]', 'n.微生物；细菌', '1. The probe is sensitive enough to detect the presence of a single microbe. 这个探针的灵敏度很高，足以测出任何微生物的存在。 2. Being small may also have helped the microbe absorb nutrients more efficiently. 体积微小同样可以帮助微生物更加有效地吸收养分。 3. A quiet meteorologist first noticed the microbe menace. 一位沉默寡言的气象学家首先注意到了细菌威胁。', '形容词: microbial');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cosmic', '[\'kɑːzmɪk]', 'adj.宇宙的；广大无边的；无限的', '1. I have mystical visions and cosmic vibrations. 我有神秘的幻觉和宇宙的震波。 2. I\'m pure, so I\'m more in touch with cosmic forces. 因为我纯洁，所以我能更好的接触宇宙的力量。', '副词: cosmically 异体字: cosmical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dam', '[dæm]', 'n.水坝；堤；障碍物 v.筑坝；抑制(情感等）', '1. The dam was not strong enough to hold back the flood waters. 水坝不太坚固，挡不住洪水。 2. The village was swept away when the dam burst. 村庄在水坝决堤时被冲走了。 3. The water deepened after the dam was built. 堤坝建成后水已加深。 4. The river keeps rising and the dam is threatened. 河水不断上涨，大堤出现险情。 5. They are going to dam up the river to set up a hydropower station. 他们准备拦江筑坝建水电站。', '名词: dammer 过去式: dammed 过去分词: dammed 现在分词: damming 第三人称单数: dams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('predict', '[prɪ\'dɪkt]', 'v.预言；预报；预知；预测', '1. It is virtually impossible to predict the future accurately. 精确预言未来的事实际上是办不到的。 2. The economists predicted an increase in the rate of inflation. 经济学家预言通货膨胀率将会增长。 3. The earthquake had been predicted several months before. 这次地震早在几个月以前就发布了预报。 4. It is impossible to predict what will happen. 预知未来的事是不可能的。', '形容词: predictable 副词: predictably 名词: predictability 过去式: predicted 过去分词: predicted 现在分词: predicting 第三人称单数: predicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prevent', '[prɪ\'vent]', 'v.预防；防止，阻止；挡住', '1. Scientists are trying to find ways to prevent disease. 科学家们正试图找到预防疾病的方法。 2. It is the job of the police to prevent crime. 防止犯罪是警察的职责。 3. Nothing can prevent us from carrying out the plan. 什么也无法阻挡我们去实施这个计划。 4. Ways must be found to prevent the poisonous gases from polluting the air. 一定要找到办法防止有毒气体污染空气。', '形容词: preventable 名词: preventability 过去式: prevented 过去分词: prevented 现在分词: preventing 第三人称单数: prevents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('controvert', '[\'kɑːntrəvɜːrt]', 'v.议论；辩驳；驳击', '1. The statement of the last witness controvert the evidence of the first two. 最后一个证人的陈述反驳了前两人的证词。 2. I shall have to controvert one or two ideas that are almost universally accepted. 我要反驳一两个几乎是公认的观点。 3. These two schools controvert against each other in domestic and foreign countries. 无论在国内还是在国外，都存在着这两种马克思哲学诠释理论的激烈争论。 4. In my opinion, the more abusive they are, the better; Anyway no amount of abuse can controvert the three points I\'ve dealt with. 我看越骂越好，我讲的这三条总是骂不倒的。', '形容词: controvertible 过去式: controverted 过去分词: controverted 现在分词: controverting 第三人称单数: controverts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('Fahrenheit', '[\'færənhaɪt]', 'n.华氏温标；华氏温度计 adj.华氏的', '1. In some countries air temperature is given in degrees of Fahrenheit. 在某些国家气温以华氏温标给出。 2. The temperature today is seventy degrees Fahrenheit. 今天气温是华氏七十度。 3. Water freezes at 32 degrees Fahrenheit. 当达到32华氏时水开始结冰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fitness', '[\'fɪtnəs]', 'n.健康；适合', '1. Good muscles are one of the prerequisites of physical fitness. 肌肉发达是身体健康的一个必备条件。 2. The long climb tested our fitness and stamina. 那次长距离爬山是对我们健康状况和耐力的考验。 3. Her fitness for the job cannot be questioned. 她能胜任这项工作，这是无庸置疑的。 4. His fitness to operate on a patient is in question. 他是否适宜为患者动手术还是个问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('smear', '[smɪr]', 'v.涂抹；弄脏；诽谤 n.污点；涂料；诽谤', '1. We smeared cream on our faces. 我们在脸上搽雪花膏。 2. You should smear your hands with grease. 你该把双手涂上油脂。 3. He smeared some balm on his hand to soothe the pain. 他在手上涂了些药膏来止痛。 4. Don\'t smear the lens; I\'ve just polished it. 别把镜头弄脏了，我刚刚擦过。 5. There was a smear of blood on the wall. 墙上有一片血迹。', '过去式: smeared 过去分词: smeared 现在分词: smearing 第三人称单数: smears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('horizontal', '[ˌhɔːrə\'zɑːntl]', 'adj.水平的；横的 n.水平线；水平面', '1. The vertical line meets the horizontal one here. 垂直线与水平线在此相交。 2. The sun rises from the horizontal line. 太阳从地平线上升起。 3. Please draw a horizontal line on the page. 请在这一页画条横线。 4. The bottom of the door is out of the horizontal. 这扇门底部不成水平。', '副词: horizontally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gulf', '[ɡʌlf]', 'n.海湾；鸿沟 vt.吞没', '1. The gulf extends northward. 海湾向北方延伸。 2. The Gulf War has sapped Iraqi vitality badly. 海湾战争使伊拉克大伤元气。 3. Thousands of ships enwombed in the gulf of mexico. 数千艘的船深藏在墨西哥海湾中。 4. Between him and Mr Smith there was a great gulf fixed. 他与史密斯之间有一道永远不可逾越的鸿沟。', '过去式: gulfed 过去分词: gulfed 现在分词: gulfing 第三人称单数: gulfs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defame', '[dɪ\'feɪm]', 'vt.诽谤；中伤；损毁名誉', '1. We expect politicians to defame each other in an election year. 我们预料政客们在选举年会互相诽谤。', '名词: defamer 过去式: defamed 过去分词: defamed 现在分词: defaming 第三人称单数: defames');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('encumber', '[ɪn\'kʌmbər]', 'v.妨害；阻害', '1. The girl\'s long skirt encumber her while running. 这女孩子的长裙在她跑的时候阻碍她的行动。 2. Objects, such as provisions or baggage, that impede or encumber. 包袱妨碍或拖累的物体，如装备或者行李 3. He is encumbered with a large family. 他被一个大家庭所拖累。 4. Travelling is difficult when you\'re encumbered with two small children and a heavy suitcase. 旅行时带着两个孩子和一个沉重的手提箱，真是寸步难行。', '过去式: encumbered 过去分词: encumbered 现在分词: encumbering 第三人称单数: encumbers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spread', '[spred]', 'v.传播；展开；散布；铺开；伸展；涂撒 n.范围；传播；差额；幅度；盛宴', '1. The radio spread the news as soon as the accident happened . 事故一发生,收音机就把这条消息传播出去了。 2. The rumor was widely spread among the crowd. 谣言在人群当中广泛地传播开来。 3. She spread her wings and flew lightly down. 她展开双翅轻轻飞下。 4. I spread my arms as far apart as I could. 我尽可能地将双臂伸展开。 5. The current survey will have a wider geographic spread. 当前的调查将在更广泛的地域范围內进行。', '形容词: spreadable 副词: spreadably 名词: spreadability 过去式: spread 过去分词: spread 现在分词: spreading 第三人称单数: spreads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('universal', '[ˌjuːnɪ\'vɜːrsl]', 'adj.普遍的；全世界的；宇宙的；全体的；通用的 n.通用原理，普遍原则', '1. These phenomena is very universal. 这些现象己经非常普遍了。 2. Overpopulation is a universal problem. 人口过多是全球性的问题。 3. Music has been called the universal language. 人们称音乐为世界的语言。 4. The doer is a universal structure. 行事者是一个宇宙的结构。 5. There are no economic universals. 英语是一种世界通用的语言。', '副词: universally 名词: universalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abdicate', '[\'æbdɪkeɪt]', 'vt.正式放弃；让位 vi.退位；辞职', '1. He was forced to abdicate his claim on the property. 他被迫放弃要求财产的权利。 2. He\'s abdicated all responsibility in the affair. 他已经放弃了这件事中的一切职责。 3. The king was forced to abdicate his throne. 国王被迫逊位。 4. King Edward VIII abdicated in 1936. 英王爱德华八世于1936年退位。', '形容词: abdicable 名词: abdication 过去式: abdicated 过去分词: abdicated 现在分词: abdicating 第三人称单数: abdicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ripe', '[raɪp]', 'adj.成熟的；熟的', '1. The branches were weighed down with ripe apples. 苹果成熟了把树枝都压弯了。 2. Most tomatoes are red when ripe, but some kinds are yellow. 大多数西红柿成熟时是红色的，但有些品种是黄色的。 3. The ripe apples picked easily. 成熟的苹果易于采摘 4. The time was ripe for a challenge to the power of the government. 时机已经成熟，可以向政府权力提出挑战了。', '副词: ripely 比较级: riper 最高级: ripest 名词: ripeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confidence', '[\'kɑːnfɪdəns]', 'n.信任；把握；信心；知心话 adj.骗得信任的', '1. The servant enjoyed his master\'s confidence. 这仆人深得主人的信赖。 2. We have full confidence that we shall succeed. 我们完全有把握取得成功。 3. The worst barrier to your success is not lack of money, but lack of confidence. 你成功最大的障碍不是缺钱,而是缺乏信心。 4. The two girls told each other confidences about their boyfriends. 这两个姑娘相互谈了关于各自男友的悄悄话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('despise', '[dɪ\'spaɪz]', 'vt.轻视', '1. He claims to despise riches. 他宣称蔑视钱财。 2. You must not despise a man because he is poor. 你不可因一个人贫穷而轻视他。 3. I despise his refusing to accept responsibility. 他拒不承担责任，我鄙视他。 4. It is incorrect to despise woman. 轻视妇女是错误的。', '名词: despisal 过去式: despised 过去分词: despised 现在分词: despising 第三人称单数: despises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perform', '[pər\'fɔːrm]', 'v.执行；履行；表演；运转；举行', '1. Every manager must perform some duties of a ceremonial nature. 每个管理者必须执行一些礼仪性的任务。 2. Student teams perform a comprehensive analysis and valuation of a business, as outlined in the syllabus. 如同课程大纲所提及，每一组学生都要对一个企业执行广泛的分析与评价。 3. They always perform their duties faithfully. 他们总是忠实地履行自己的职责。 4. We will resolutely perform our internationalist duty no matter what happens. 不管发生什么情况，我们都要坚决履行我们的国际主义义务。', '形容词: performable 名词: performer 过去式: performed 过去分词: performed 现在分词: performing 第三人称单数: performs 名词: performance');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seclusion', '[sɪ\'kluːʒn]', 'n.隔离；隔绝；隐居', '1. The jury arrives at its verdict in the seclusion of the jury room. 陪审团在隔离的评议室里作出裁定。 2. I live very much in seclusion these days. 这些天我过着几乎与世隔绝的生活。 3. The famous actor now lives in seclusion. 那位著名的演员现在过着隐居生活。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blink', '[blɪŋk]', 'v.眨眼；闪烁；拒绝承认或面对；用闪光灯传送信号 n.眨眼；闪光；一瞬间', '1. The TV announcer never seems to blink. 这个电视广播员似乎从来都不眨眼。 2. Women blink twice as much as man. 女人眨眼的次数是男人的两倍。 3. The lights were blinking on the horizon. 灯光在地平线上闪烁着。 4. You cannot blink the fact that there are wars. 你不能无视于战争存在的事实。 5. She doesnot comprehend the meaning of my blink. 她没有领会我眨眼的意思。', '过去式: blinked 过去分词: blinked 现在分词: blinking 第三人称单数: blinks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('democrat', '[\'deməkræt]', 'n.民主主义者 Democrat. n.美国民主党派的成员', '1. A democrat usually gets the union\'s endorsement. 民主主义者通常都得到工会的支持。 2. The democrat endeavored to accomplish his aim by himself. 那个民主主义者致力于独自达成他的目标。 3. The President is a Democrat. 总统是民主党员。 4. The man is neither fish nor fowl; he votes Democrat or Republican according to which will do him the most good. 这个人在左右摇摆，他投民主党的票还是共和党的票得看哪个党对他更有益处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brisk', '[brɪsk]', 'adj.敏锐的；活泼的；活跃的；轻快的；凛冽的 v.（使）轻快', '1. His movements were brisk and boyish. 他的动作仍很敏捷，孩子气。 2. He was a vigorous, brisk person. 他是一个强壮的，活泼有力的人。 3. Diana \'s brisk, commanding voice rang out from a passage way. 黛安娜活泼而威严的声音从一条过道中传了出来。 4. Trading was brisk on the Stock Exchangetoday. 今日证券交易所交投活跃。 5. He brisked up his pace at the beautiful sight. 看到那美丽的景色，他加快了脚步。', '副词: briskly 比较级: brisker 最高级: briskest 名词: briskness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('neolithic', '[ˌniːə\'lɪθɪk]', 'adj.新石器时代的', '1. Cattle were first domesticated in Neolithic times. 新石器时代有人开始驯养牛。 2. By 10,000 BC, most of mankind was at the Neolithic level. 到公元前 10000年，大部分人类已经处于新石器时代的水平。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('documentation', '[ˌdɑːkjumen\'teɪʃn]', 'n.文件；证明文件；史实；[计]文件编制', '1. For netmeeting instructions refer to microsoft\'s documentation or online help. 关于NetMeeting指南，可参考Microsoft文档或在线帮助。 2. Concentrate your order with us save you money on postage, cable, freight, documentation, etc. 如集中向我公司采购，能节省您在邮递、电报、运输以及提供单证等方面的各项费用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idol', '[\'aɪdl]', 'n.偶像 n.菩萨', '1. The pop singer is the idol of young people. 这位流行歌手成为年轻人崇拜的偶像。 2. The youngsters greeted their idol with a hail. 那群年轻人向他们的偶像欢呼致敬。 3. Don\'t make an idol of money. 不要崇拜财富。 4. The set includes a golden fertility idol pen holder, an Ark of the Convenant business card holder and a Holy Grail paperclip holder. 该套桌饰包括一个催子菩萨形状的金色笔筒，一个方舟形状的合同名片夹和一个圣杯形状的回形针收集器。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nervous', '[\'nɜːrvəs]', 'adj.神经的，神经细胞的，神经性的；焦虑的；神经质的，紧张的，不安的；易兴奋的', '1. The doctors shall operate on his central nervous system. 医生们将要对他的中枢神经系统动手术。 2. He is suffering from nervous tension. 他正受神经紧张之苦。 3. They can also help come calm and control nervous horses and got cheap guard sheep and gots goats on farms. 它们也可以使紧张焦虑的马平静下来，它们同样可以保卫绵羊和山羊。 4. The merest little thing makes him nervous. 最微不足道的小事也会使他紧张。', '副词: nervously 名词: nervousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dexterous', '[\'dekstrəs]', 'adj.灵巧的；机灵的；惯用右手的 =dextrous.', '1. A good pianist must be dexterous. 一个好的钢琴家必须要灵巧。 2. The manager was dexterous in handling his staff. 那位经理善于运用他属下的职员。 3. The English Minister can often gain a point by dexterous dealing in Parliament. 英国的内阁成员在议会中以巧妙应付的手段往往可以获得成功。', '副词: dexterously 异体字: dextrous 名词: dexterousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('synthetic', '[sɪn\'θetɪk]', 'adj.合成的；人造的；综合的；虚伪的 n.合成物；人工制品', '1. The basin is made of synthetic resin. 这个盆是用合成树脂做的。 2. Some of the new synthetic dress materials do not crush . 有些新型合成衣料不会起皱。 3. The clerk passed off a synthetic diamond to that unsuspecting customer. 这个店员用人造钻石冒充真货卖给了那个轻信的顾客。 4. Latin is a synthetic language, while English is analytic. 拉丁文是一种综合性语言,而英语是一种分析性语言。 5. Corticosteroids and their synthetic analogs are used to treat rheumatism and other inflammatory ailments. 皮质类固醇及其合成物可用来治疗风湿病和其它炎症。', '副词: synthetically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lasting', '[\'læstɪŋ]', 'adj.永久的；永恒的 动词last的现在分词.', '1. This agreement will pave the way for a lasting peace. 这个协议将为持久和平铺路。 2. I hope you will strike up a lasting friendship. 我希望你们将建立起永久的友谊。 3. Her face left a lasting impression on me. 她的脸让我留下了永恒的印象。 4. Nothing can break the lasting friendship between us. 没有任何东西能破坏我们的永恒友谊。', '副词: lastingly 名词: lastingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('peril', '[\'perəl]', 'n.危险；冒险 vt.冒险', '1. These birds are able to survive the perils of the Arctic winter. 这些鸟能在北极寒冷的冬天里生存。 2. The ship was in imminent peril of being wrecked. 那条船马上就有失事的危险。 3. You had better not invest so much money at your peril. 你最好不要冒险投资这么多。 4. He made the experiment at his peril. 他冒险做这个试验。 5. Do you think I am going to peril my reputation for you? 你以为我会为你拿我的名誉冒险?', '过去式: periled/perilled 过去分词: periled/perilled 现在分词: periling/perilling 第三人称单数: perils/perils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constellation', '[ˌkɒnstə\'leɪʃən]', 'n.星座；星群', '1. A constellation is a stellar system. 一个星座就是一个恒星星系。 2. The dragon constellation was visible in the sky. 在天空中可以看到龙星座。 3. The Great Riff of the Summer Milky Way splites the constellation. 夏日，星群被银河中的不发光的分子尘雾分开。', '形容词: constellational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('land', '[lænd]', 'n.陆地；国土；土地 v.靠岸；着陆；跌落地面；得到；使靠岸；使着陆', '1. We are glad to be on land again. 我们很高兴又踏上陆地了。 2. The river passes through our land. 这条河流经我们的国土 3. The land is laid down with red or white clover. 这块土地种上了红花和白花苜蓿。 4. This land was reclaimed from the sea. 这块土地是填海开垦出来的。 5. The ship landed safely in the end. 船最后平安靠岸了。', '过去式: landed 过去分词: landed 现在分词: landing 第三人称单数: lands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deem', '[diːm]', 'v.认为；视作', '1. They were deemed to be illegal immigrants. 他们被认为是不法移民。 2. They deemed that he was no longer capable of managing the business. 他们认为他没有能力再继续管理这个公司了。 3. These buildings are deemed to be of architectural importance and must be protected. 这些楼房被视为具有建筑的重要性', '过去式: deemed 过去分词: deemed 现在分词: deeming 第三人称单数: deems');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grateful', '[\'ɡreɪtfl]', 'adj.感激的；令人愉快的', '1. I can\'t express how grateful I am. 我说不出我有多么感激。 2. These refugees are very grateful to the government\'s succor. 这些难民非常感激政府的救援。 3. I am grateful for all your past kindness. 多蒙关照,万分感激。 4. I\'d be grateful if you should let me know as soon as possible. 你若能让我尽快知道,我会很感激的。', '副词: gratefully 名词: gratefulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kennel', '[\'kenl]', 'n.狗舍；养狗场；排水道 v.置于狗舍；宿于狗舍', '1. Their dog Rover lives in a kennel in the back garden. 他们的小狗罗佛的窝在后花园。 2. Sporting dogs should be kept out of doors in a kennel. 猎狗应该养在户外的狗窝中。 3. We put the dog into a kennel when we go on holiday. 我们去度假时把狗送到养狗场寄养。 4. This Kennel Club took care of the pedigree of the Border Collie. 这个养狗俱乐部照顾纯种的边境牧羊犬。 5. The old dog have no energy to go out, but kennel all day. 这只老狗无精力出去，只好整天待在狗舍里。', '过去式: kenneled/kennelled 过去分词: kenneled/kennelled 现在分词: kenneling/kennelling 第三人称单数: kennels/kennels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('productivity', '[ˌprɑːdʌk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.生产率；生产力', '1. We should aim with efforts for higher productivity. 我们应该力争达到更高的生产率。 2. This will help do away with heavy manual labour and raise productivity. 这可以帮助消除繁重的体力劳动，提高劳动生产率。 3. Improved productivity justifies an increase in wages. 提高了生产力理应增加工资。 4. The workers are trying their best to increase productivity. 工人们正竭尽全力提高生产力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('towering', '[\'taʊərɪŋ]', 'adj.高耸的；激烈的；杰出的 动词tower的现在分词形式.', '1. They built a TV tower on the towering hill. 他们在高耸的山顶建起了一座电视塔。 2. The living room is bedimmed by the towering trees outside. 室外高耸的树木，于客厅显得昏暗。', '副词: toweringly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enforce', '[ɪn\'fɔːrs]', 'vt.强迫；强制；实施；执行；加强', '1. You can\'t enforce cooperation between the players. 队员间的配合并非强迫命令而成。 2. Don\'t enforce your will on the child, please. 请别把你的意愿强加给这孩子。 3. Contracts are promises that the law will enforce. 合同是可强制执行的一项或一组诺言。 4. It may be possible to enforce part of a contract. 合同可以部分被强制执行。', '形容词: enforceable 名词: enforceability 过去式: enforced 过去分词: enforced 现在分词: enforcing 第三人称单数: enforces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dwell', '[dwel]', 'vi.居住；存在；冥想；详细阐述', '1. He decided to dwell on our island. 他决定到我们的岛上居住。 2. I own two flats where I used to dwell alternately. 我拥有两个居所并一直交替地居住。 3. How his words dwell in my mind! 他的一席话在我的脑海里经久难忘。 4. They dwelled in joy. 他们沉浸于欢乐之中。', '名词: dweller 过去式: dwelt/dwelled 过去分词: dwelt/dwelled 现在分词: dwelling 第三人称单数: dwells');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spiral', '[\'spaɪrəl]', 'n.螺旋；螺旋形之物；不断恶化、增加或减少 v.螺旋移动；盘旋上升；不断恶化、增加或减少 adj.螺旋形的；盘旋的', '1. Society invariably moves forward in a spiral. 社会的运动总是采取螺旋形前进的。 2. This caused a downward spiral into depression. 这使经济下滑恶化为经济萧条。 3. The smoke spiraled upwards. 那股烟袅袅上升。 4. Prices are still spiralling. 价格仍然在急剧上涨。 5. A snails shell is spiral in form. 蜗牛的外壳形状是螺旋形的。', '副词: spirally 名词: spirality 过去式: spiraled/spiralled 过去分词: spiraled/spiralled 现在分词: spiraling/spiralling 第三人称单数: spirals/spirals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('isolated', '[\'aɪsəleɪtɪd]', 'adj.孤立的；隔离的；分离的 动词isolate的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Unfortunately, this is not an isolated incident. 不幸的是,这并不是一个孤立的事件。 2. The enemy was holed up in a few isolated strongholds. 敌人龟缩在几个孤立的据点里。 3. As an independent republic, they would be politically and economically isolated. 作为一个独立共和体,他们在政治和经济上被隔离。 4. There is a strong spirit of fraternity among these isolated people. 这些与世隔绝的人之间有强烈的兄弟般的情谊。 5. Scientists have isolated the virus causing the epidemic. 科学家们已分离出引起这种流行病的病毒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intermediate', '[ˌɪntər\'miːdiət]', 'adj.中间的；中级的 n.中间体；调解人；媒介物 vi.调解；干涉', '1. Term from the intermediate user or group. 以后的术语从中间的用户或组来计算下一个术语。 2. Intermediate arrays have porosities falling between these limits. 中间的排列方式，孔隙率介于这两个值之间。 3. I\'ve passed the intermediate level exam of Japanese. 我已经通过了日语的中级水平考试。 4. What is the structure of this intermediate? 这个中间产物的结构是怎样的?', '副词: intermediately 名词: intermediacy 过去式: intermediated 过去分词: intermediated 现在分词: intermediating 第三人称单数: intermediates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('absence', '[\'æbsəns]', 'n.缺席；缺乏', '1. His long absence raised fears about his safety. 他长期不在引起了大家对他的安全的担心。 2. What was the real reason for your absence? 你缺席的真正原因是什么？ 3. We are in the absence of experience. 我们缺乏经验。 4. The absence of color in that drawing make it dull. 那幅画因没有着色而显得晦暗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grip', '[ɡrɪp]', 'n.紧握；手提包；了解；手柄 vt.吸引；紧抓', '1. The eagle seized its prey in a tenacious grip. 鹰将捕获物紧紧抓住。 2. The child would not let go his grip on Tom. 这孩子紧紧地抓住汤姆不放。 3. He kept a firm grip on his children. 他对小孩管得很严。 4. It is a leather grip. 这是一个皮制手提包。 5. The audience were gripped by the play. 这群观众被这部戏剧吸引住了。', '副词: grippingly 名词: gripper 过去式: gripped 过去分词: gripped 现在分词: gripping 第三人称单数: grips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disburse', '[dɪs\'bɜːrs]', 'v.支付；支出；分配', '1. We disburse payments to members on a monthly basis. 我们支付款项成员在每月的基础。 2. Receive and disburse money in establishments other than financial institutions. 负责公司和相关财务机构的资金收付。 3. Trials to disburse official business expenses with credit cards continued. 推进公务卡管理试点。 4. On approval, we will disburse the fund to your designated bank account directly. 一经批核，贷款将于扣除手续费后直接存入您指定的银行账户。', '形容词: disbursable 名词: disburser 过去式: disbursed 过去分词: disbursed 现在分词: disbursing 第三人称单数: disburses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('position', '[pə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.位置；职位；立场；状态 vt.安置；定位', '1. Can you find our position on this map? 你能在这幅地图上找到我们的位置吗? 2. I can tell the time from the position of the sun. 我可以从太阳的位置知道时刻。 3. The position of manager is still open. 经理职位仍然空缺。 4. He got the position on the strength of his skill in finance. 他凭著自己的理财本领得到了这个职位。 5. She positioned herself near the warm fire. 她待在温暖的炉子的旁边。', '形容词: positional 副词: positionally 名词: positioner 过去式: positioned 过去分词: positioned 现在分词: positioning 第三人称单数: positions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('auction', '[\'ɔːkʃn]', 'n.拍卖 vt.拍卖', '1. We will put the car up for auction. 我们将把这辆小车拍卖。 2. The picture should fetch 2000 pounds at auction. 这张画拍卖可得2000英镑。 3. We had a private view of the jewels before the public auction. 那些珠宝公开拍卖以前我们私下看了预展。 4. They will auction off a collection of oils. 他们将拍卖一批收藏的油画。', '过去式: auctioned 过去分词: auctioned 现在分词: auctioning 第三人称单数: auctions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('talent', '[\'tælənt]', 'n.天赋；才能，才艺；天才；人才；<英俚>美人', '1. He has great talent, but he has lost his faith. 他很有天赋，但是他已经丧失了信心。 2. The mother found that her son had a musical talent. 母亲发现儿子有音乐天赋。 3. Her talents are well known. 人人都知道她很有才干。 4. His talent was largely self-developed. 他的才能主要是自己培养的。', '形容词: talented 名词: talentlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('simmer', '[\'sɪmə(r)]', 'v.炖；煨；即将爆发；内心充满 n.炖；即将发作', '1. Simmer the stew for an hour. 用文火把菜炖一小时。 2. Keep the potatoes on the simmer for ten minutes. 把马铃薯炖十分钟。 3. Allow the soup to simmer gently for ten minutes. 把汤小火煨上10 分钟。 4. This row has been simmering for months. 这场争吵已憋了好几个月了。 5. Give the vegetables a five-minute simmer. 把菜炖五分钟。', '过去式: simmered 过去分词: simmered 现在分词: simmering 第三人称单数: simmers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invalidate', '[ɪn\'vælɪdeɪt]', 'vt.使无效；使作废', '1. The making of false statements could result in the invalidation of the contract. 提供虚假资料可能导致合同失效。', '名词: invalidation 过去式: invalidated 过去分词: invalidated 现在分词: invalidating 第三人称单数: invalidates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('install', '[ɪn\'stɔːl]', 'vt.安装；安置；使 ... 就职', '1. She installed her air-conditioner without help by herself. 她自己安装了空调。 2. The workers are installing a heating system. 工人们正在安装供暖系统。 3. It is necessary that you install a burglar alarm. 你有必要装防盗警报器。 4. The children are comfortably installed in a new home. 孩子们在新居舒适地安顿下来。', '名词: installer');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strenuous', '[\'strenjuəs]', 'adj.奋发的；费力的；繁重的；积极的', '1. He made strenuous efforts to improve his reading. 他奋发努力提高阅读能力。 2. I\'ll appreciate your strenuous effort to promote the sale in your market on commission basis. 在市场上为我们的产品尽全力促销的话,我将非常感谢您。 3. She made strenuous efforts to tame her anger. 她竭力压制心头怒火。 4. I\'ll appreciate your strenuous effort to promote the sale in your market on commission basis. 在市场上为我们的产品尽全力促销的话,我将非常感谢您。', '副词: strenuously 名词: strenuosity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pebble', '[\'pebl]', 'n.鹅卵石 n.水晶；水晶透镜 v.用卵石铺；用卵石投掷；使有卵石纹', '1. On the way, Hansel dropped a pebble every several meters. 一路上，亨舍儿每隔几米就扔一块鹅卵石。 2. The son put his hand into the moneybag and drew out a pebble. 儿子把手伸进钱袋中，拿出了一粒鹅卵石。', '形容词: pebbly 过去式: pebbled 过去分词: pebbled 现在分词: pebbling 第三人称单数: pebbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('potential', '[pə\'tenʃl]', 'adj.潜在的；可能的 n.潜力；潜能 n.电位；电势', '1. These potential effects must be studied carefully. 这些潜在的影响必须仔细地加以研究。 2. Aha! Now that \'s something that has potential . 啊！ 现在这好像是很有可能的。 3. She has acting potential, but she needs training. 她有表演潜力，但需要训练。 4. He hasn\'t realized his full potential yet. 他还没有意识到他的全部潜能。 5. We can only measure the difference between the potentials of two half cells when they are linked to form an electrochemical cell. 当两个半电池连接形成一个化学电池时,我们仅能测定两个半电池之间电位的差值。', '副词: potentially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chamber', '[\'tʃeɪmbər]', 'n.室；会议厅；房间 adj.【音】室内的，小型的；私人的，秘密的', '1. The heart has four chambers. 心脏有两房两室。 2. Most of the meetings are held in the council chamber of city hall. 大多数的会议都在市政大厅的理事会议室举行。 3. The judge met the two lawyers in his chamber. 法官在他的办公室里会见了两位律师。', '过去式: chambered 过去分词: chambered 现在分词: chambering 第三人称单数: chambers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repertoire', '[\'repərtwɑːr]', 'n.全部节目；全部才能', '1. A repertoire of tricks will astound the esteemed public. 全部节目将使尊敬的观众惊心动魄。 2. That tune is not in my repertoire. 我演出的节目中没有这个曲子。 3. He has a wide repertoire of dirty jokes. 他一肚子下流笑话. 4. Julia has a vast repertoire of smiles. 朱莉娅具有驾御各式微笑的本领。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('variation', '[ˌveri\'eɪʃn]', 'n.变种；变奏曲；变动；变化', '1. Finally, the cherry in Fujian Wuyi Mountain should be treated as a new variation of Cerasus subhirtella in taxonomy. 最后，建议在分类学关系上将福建武夷山野生早樱做为大叶早樱新变种处理。 2. This is a set of variations on a theme by Mozart. 这是以莫扎特某一乐曲为主题的一组变奏曲。 3. Prices are subject to variation. 价格可以变动。 4. The dial records showed a very slight variation in pressure. 刻度盘显示出压力有极微小的变化。', '形容词: variational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fellowship', '[\'feloʊʃɪp]', 'n.友谊；团体；会员资格；奖学金', '1. They offer students counselling and fellowship. 他们向学生提供辅导并伸出友谊之手。 2. They offered him the hand of fellowship when he was in difficulties. 当他身处困境时，他们向他伸出了友谊之手。 3. Aleck belonged to a fellowship of revenge. 亚力克属于一个报仇团体。 4. After their initial expedition to Dujiangyan, members of Mr Sun\'s fellowship were soon faced with a number of organisational and logistical constraints. 在抵达都江堰后不久，成都天主教青年团体的成员就遇到了许多组织与后勤方面的约束。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mobile', '[\'moʊbl]', 'adj.移动的；易变的；活动的 n.<美>汽车；可动雕塑；悬挂饰物；活动物体', '1. Additionally, consumers continue to embrace mobile personal devices. 此外,消费者接受移动个人设备的热情依然不减。 2. He had a mobile, expressive, animated face. 他有一张多变的，富于表情的，生动活泼的脸。 3. He has a broken leg and isn\'t very mobile. 他的腿摔伤了,活动不便。 4. A specially equipped car makes a handicapped person more mobile. 有特殊装置的汽车使得残障者比以前更易于活动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decay', '[dɪ\'keɪ]', 'v.(使)衰退；(使)腐败；(使)腐烂 n.衰退；腐烂；腐败', '1. Naomi: Your entire body is begining to decay. 直美:你的整个身体都在衰退。 2. What made the Roman Empire decay? 罗马帝国为何衰亡？ 3. The dampness of the climate decayed the books. 气候潮湿，把书都霉坏了。 4. The vegetables have begun to decay. 那些蔬菜已开始腐烂。 5. His mental decay is distressing. 他的智力衰退令人苦恼。', '名词: decayer 过去式: decayed 过去分词: decayed 现在分词: decaying 第三人称单数: decays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('livelihood', '[\'laɪvlihʊd]', 'n.生计；营生；生活', '1. Mowing lawns is his only livelihood. 他仅靠给人家草坪除草维持生计。 2. I like playing in the band, but I don\'t do it just for fun; it\'s my livelihood. 我喜欢在乐队里演奏，但这不只是为了好玩，而是我的谋生之道。 3. She earns a livelihood by sewing. 她靠缝纫谋生。 4. They didn\'t care for the livelihood of the people. 他们不关心群众的生活。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relay', '[\'riːleɪ]', 'vt.转播；转达；中继；接力；接替 n.继电器；接力赛；替班', '1. Images of the war were relayed around the world. 世界各地转播了战争的图像。 2. I will relay your opinion to the headmaster. 我愿把你的意见转告校长。 3. The Relay Agent could not start up its main thread. 中继代理无法启动其主线程。 4. Frame Relay Connection and Traffic Flow Control. 帧中继连接和流量控制。 5. This relay connects one input to one output. 该继电器将一个输入连接到一个输出。', '过去式: relayed 过去分词: relayed 现在分词: relaying 第三人称单数: relays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perpetuate', '[pər\'petʃueɪt]', 'vt.使永存；使不朽', '1. These measures will perpetuate the hostility between the two groups. 采取这些措施势必使那两集团永远对立。 2. They decided to perpetuate the memory of their leader by erecting a statue. 他们为永远纪念那位领袖决定建一座雕像。', '名词: perpetuance 过去式: perpetuated 过去分词: perpetuated 现在分词: perpetuating 第三人称单数: perpetuates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('paste', '[peɪst]', 'n.面团；浆糊；糊状物；糊 vt.裱糊；粘贴', '1. The boy squeezed paste into a ball . 孩子把面团捏成了球形。 2. We used paste to attach our designs to the poster. 我们用浆糊把我们设计的图案贴在招贴牌上。 3. He beat the mixture up to a paste. 他把混合料搅成糊状。 4. Stir the flour and milk to a stiff paste. 把面粉和牛奶搅成很稠的糊。 5. She pasted the pictures into a scrapbook. 她把图片贴在剪贴簿上。', '过去式: pasted 过去分词: pasted 现在分词: pasting 第三人称单数: pastes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('notion', '[\'noʊʃn]', 'n.观念；概念；想法；主张', '1. State control is a very un-American notion. 实行国家控制是根本违背美国观念的。 2. They want a system based on the notions of personal equality and liberty. 他们想要基于人的平等﹑ 自由等概念的制度。 3. We had a notion that he was telling a lie. 我们当时的看法是他在说谎。 4. She dinged the notion into our ears. 她老是唠唠叨叨地跟我们讲那个想法。(或：她把那个想法反反复复地灌输给我们)。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extant', '[ek\'stænt]', 'adj.现存的', '1. This law is ancient but still extant. 这一法律古老但仍然有效。 2. This is the extant manuscript of the poem. 这是现存的该诗的原稿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attendant', '[ə\'tendənt]', 'adj.伴随的 n.服务员；出席者；伴随物；侍从', '1. An unexpected accident is attendant upon carelessness. 粗心大意将导致意外事故发生。 2. Miseries are attendant on violence. 暴力往往会带来种种的不幸。 3. If you need anything, just ring for the attendant. 如果您要什么，就按铃叫服务员。 4. I asked the attendant to conduct him out. 我让服务员领他出去。', '副词: attendantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('superior', '[suː\'pɪriər]', 'n.上级；高手；上标 adj.高傲的；上层的；上好的；出众的', '1. He always does what his superiors tell him. 他惟上级之命是从。 2. He has no superior as a Shakespearian actor. 他演莎士比亚戏剧无出其右。 3. He smiled a superior smile as he drove past in his expensive new car. 他开着那辆豪华的新车驶过时，傲慢的微微一笑。 4. I\'ll report you to your superior officer! 我要把你的情况报告给你的上司！', '副词: superiorly 名词: superiority');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scandal', '[\'skændl]', 'n.丑闻；反感；耻辱；中伤', '1. The scandal caused tempests in the newspaper. 那件丑闻在报纸上引起阵阵风波。 2. The villagers knew about the scandal. 村子里的居民知道这件丑事。 3. This scandal may topple the government. 这桩丑闻有可能使政府垮台。 4. The President is at the center of a recent scandal over revelation about his financial interests. 总统因近来被揭露涉嫌金融权益问题而成为丑闻的主角。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beneficiary', '[ˌbenɪ\'fɪʃieri]', 'n.受惠者；受益人', '1. I am the beneficiary of your generosity. 我是你慷慨大方的受益人。 2. Beneficiary must sign on the certificate. 受益人必须在证书上签字。 3. Her husband was the chief beneficiary of her will. 她丈夫是她遗嘱的主要受益人。 4. His granddaughter is the beneficiary of the trust. 他的祖父是信托物的受益人。', '名词复数: beneficiaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flee', '[fliː]', 'vi.逃走；消失；逃避；(时间)飞逝 vt.逃离', '1. He tried to flee from the police in a stolen car. 他企图驾驶一辆偷来的车从警察局逃走。 2. The frightened people fled from the fire. 人们惊恐万状地逃离了火灾现场。 3. The mists was fleeing before the rising sun. 太阳慢慢升起，薄雾渐渐消失。 4. He should not flee from responsibility. 他不应逃避责任。 5. He was caught trying to flee the country. 他企图逃离该国时被抓住了。', '名词: fleer 过去式: fled 过去分词: fled 现在分词: fleeing 第三人称单数: flees');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commerce', '[\'kɑːmɜːrs]', 'n.贸易；商业', '1. We must promote commerce with neighbouring countries. 我们必须促进与邻国的贸易。 2. Our country has been trying to broaden its commerce with other nations. 我国一直在努力扩大与其他国家的贸易往来。 3. In USA, NewYork City is the chief seat of commerce. 在美国,纽约是主要的商业中心。 4. Banks are the nerves of commerce. 银行是商业的中枢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inner', '[\'ɪnər]', 'adj.内心的；内部的；里面的 n.里面', '1. He has no inner resources and hates being alone. 他没有内在的精神寄托，因而害怕孤独。 2. Her artificial gaiety disguised an inner sadness. 她以矫揉造作的快乐掩饰著内心的悲痛。 3. I no longer felt the inner restraint. 我再也不感到内心的压抑了。 4. Does it ever occur to you to use your sight to see into the inner nature of a friend or acquaintance? 你曾否想到用你的视觉去探视一位朋友或认识的人的内在本性？ 5. Time is therefore always ticking in our inner ear. 因此时间总是在我们内耳里面滴滴答答地走。', '副词: innerly 名词: innerness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('economical', '[ˌiːkə\'nɑːmɪkl]', 'adj.节俭的；经济的；合算的', '1. She is an economical housekeeper and feeds her family cheaply. 她是一个节俭的家庭主妇，她全家的花销不大。 2. We are advocate economical life. 我们提倡俭朴的生活。 3. This is not an economical method of heating. 这不是一种经济的取暖方式。 4. She writes novels with economical style. 她以简练的风格写小说。', '副词: economically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attend', '[ə\'tend]', 'v.出席；参加；照料；注意；专心于', '1. I shall be attending the meeting. 我会参加会议。 2. During summer vacations some teachers attend seminars at college. 暑假里,一些教师在学院里参加研究班。 3. You\'re going out? But who will attend to the baby? 你要出去?那谁来照料这婴儿。 4. Attend to what your teacher says. 注意听老师的话。', '名词: attender 过去式: attended 过去分词: attended 现在分词: attending 第三人称单数: attends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('promising', '[\'prɑːmɪsɪŋ]', 'adj.有希望的；有前途的', '1. After a promising start, the project soon fizzled out. 这项计划开始时很有希望,但不久就失败了。 2. For a time he was looked on as a promising writer. 人们一度认为他是一个有希望的作家。 3. The results of the experiments are very promising. 实验的结果充满了希望。 4. The coach is bringing on some promising youngsters in the reserve team. 教练正在帮助后备队中有前途的年轻人提高技术。', '副词: promisingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('antagonist', '[æn\'tæɡənɪst]', 'n.敌手；对手；[医]对抗剂，拮抗剂 ；[生]对抗肌', '1. The knight defeated each antagonist. 那位骑士打败了每一个敌手。 2. He wondered what his antagonist was doing. 他不知道他的敌手在做些什么。 3. He ripped into his antagonist with fury. 他向他的对手猛扑过去。 4. I am bound to furnish my antagonists with arguments, but not with comprehension. 我一定要向对手提供争论点，但并无予以理解的必要。', '形容词: antagonistic 副词: antagonistically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('telegraph', '[\'telɪɡræf]', 'n.电报；电报机 vt.打电报；显示', '1. It was in an obscure warehouse on Telegraph Road. 那是电报路上一座不明显的仓库。 2. Telegraph to her parents at once. 立即给她父母打电报。 3. Send the message on the telegraph. 这个消息用电报机发出。 4. A teleprinter is really a machine which sends a typewriter message over a telegraph circuit. 打字电报机实际上是一种在电报电路上传送打印信息的机器。', '名词: telegrapher 过去式: telegraphed 过去分词: telegraphed 现在分词: telegraphing 第三人称单数: telegraphs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inn', '[ɪn]', 'n.客栈；小旅店', '1. There was an air of romance about the old inn. 这家老客栈颇有些浪漫气氛。 2. I intend to strike my staff at that small inn. 我打算在那家客栈暂住下来。 3. The traveller decided to lie at an inn that night. 旅行者决定那天晚上在一个小旅店过夜。 4. My girl friend enjoys traveling through the country hailing up at the nearest inn. 我的女朋友喜欢乡间旅行，夜宿就近的小旅店。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prosper', '[\'prɑːspər]', 'vi.繁盛；成功；兴旺', '1. We are bound to prosper beyond other countries. 我们肯定要比其他国家更兴旺繁荣。 2. The schemes of the wicked often prosper. 坏人的阴谋常常得逞。 3. She can\'t prosper on the course she\'s going now. 她现在所走的路是没有前途的。 4. With her at the wheel, the company began to prosper. 有了她当主管，公司开始兴旺起来。', '过去式: prospered 过去分词: prospered 现在分词: prospering 第三人称单数: prospers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('competence', '[\'kɑːmpɪtəns]', 'n.能力；胜任；管辖权', '1. Competence is prerequisite to promotion. 能力是升职的先决条件。 2. I doubt his competence to do the work. 我怀疑他是否有能力做那件工作。 3. No one doubts her competence as a teacher. 谁也不怀疑她能胜任教师工作。 4. It has beyond the competence of the court. 它已经超出法院的权限。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aerial', '[\'eriəl]', 'adj.空中的；空气的；航空的；空想的 n.天线', '1. He showed me some aerial photographs. 他给我看了一些空中拍摄的照片。 2. Aerial pollution is a problem that should be solved quickly. 空气污染是一个亟待解决的问题。 3. Airline is the service industry that offers the aerial affair of transport service. 航空公司属于提供航空运输业务的服务行业。 4. The birds perched on the television aerial. 鸟停在电视天线上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('court', '[kɔːrt]', 'n.法院；庭院；宫廷；球场；奉承 v.献殷勤；追求；招致；设法获得', '1. Sherman recommended that Clarke be disciplined, but higher-ups rejected the idea. 谢尔曼建议对克拉克进行纪律惩戒，但高层拒绝了这个意见。 2. My court is deserted but I do not care. 我的庭院一片荒芜但是我无心照看。 3. The court of King Solomon was noted for its splendor. 所罗门国王的宫廷以其华丽著称。 4. The court moves to the country in the summer. 夏天王室上下都移居到乡下去。 5. He has been courting the director, hoping to get the leading role in the play. 他一直在讨好导演，想在剧中扮演主角。', '过去式: courted 过去分词: courted 现在分词: courting 第三人称单数: courts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comparable', '[\'kɑːmpərəbl]', 'adj.可比较的；比得上的', '1. The achievements of an athlete and a writer are not comparable. 运动员的成就与作家的成就不能相提并论。 2. The sets of figures are not comparable. 这几组数字是不可比的。 3. Your achievements are comparable with his. 你的成绩可与他的相媲美。 4. His handwriting is not bad, but it\'s hardly comparable with yours. 他的书法不错，但是很难和你的相比。', '副词: comparably 名词: comparability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shift', '[ʃɪft]', 'v.移动；改变；换挡；字型转换 n.轮班；变化；移动；计谋；轮班职工', '1. The tools shift around in the car boot every time we turn a corner. 我们每次转弯，汽车行李箱里的工具就来回动。 2. The Left is shifting their ground. 左派正在改变立场。 3. You have to shift as you drive around the corner. 你拐角时要换挡变速。 4. They were taking turns to be on the night shift. 他们轮流做夜班。', '名词: shifter 过去式: shifted 过去分词: shifted 现在分词: shifting 第三人称单数: shifts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('approach', '[ə\'proʊtʃ]', 'v.靠近；接近；接洽；要求；达到；动手处理 n.途径；方法；接近；接洽；要求；路径；进场着陆；相似的事物', '1. He still had not the courage to approach her. 他仍没有勇气靠近她。 2. Such people as are friendly are easy to approach. 亲切之人容易接近。 3. She approached the bank for a loan. 她向银行要求贷款。 4. There is no one who even approaches his talents. 目前还没有谁的能力能与他媲美。 5. Narration should become a basic approach to preschool education. 叙事应是幼儿教育的基本途径。', '过去式: approached 过去分词: approached 现在分词: approaching 第三人称单数: approaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('surplus', '[\'sɜːrpləs]', 'n.过剩；顺差；盈余 adj.过剩的；多余的', '1. Mexico has a large surplus of oil. 墨西哥有大量过剩的石油。 2. Countries with surplus are called creditor nations. 有顺差的国家则称为债权国。 3. Surpluses of food can be sold for cash. 多余的食物可卖钱。 4. Every country has a lot of surplus labor. 每个国家都有大量的剩余劳动力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('density', '[\'densəti]', 'n.密度；浓度；比重', '1. Mercury has a much greater density than water. 水银的密度比水大得多。 2. The density of population in this city is very high. 这个城市的人口密度非常高。 3. The driver had to stop because the density of the fog made it difficult to see. 由於浓雾使道路很难看清,司机不得不停车。 4. The next trail would require a slightly higher filling density acid. 在下一次试验时需要注入比重较高的酸。', '名词复数: densities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gash', '[ɡæʃ]', 'n.深的伤口(裂缝等） v.（使）负深伤', '1. He was bleeding from a gash on his head. 他头上的伤口在出血。 2. I was frightened when I saw the nasty gash in her arm. 她胳膊上又深又长的大伤口吓坏了我。 3. He gashed his foot on a piece of broken glass. 他的脚在一块碎玻璃上划了一个大口子。', '过去式: gashed 过去分词: gashed 现在分词: gashing 第三人称单数: gashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jog', '[dʒɑːɡ]', 'v.慢跑；轻推；（使）颠簸前行 n.慢跑；轻推；颠簸', '1. He goes jogging every night. 他每晚慢跑。 2. You jogged my elbow and spoiled what I was drawing. 你撞到了我的手肘，弄坏了我正在画的图画。 3. The wagon jogged along on the rough road. 马车沿着崎岖不平的道路颠簸前行。 4. I go for a jog in the park every morning. 每天早晨我在公园里慢跑。', '名词: jogger 过去式: jogged 过去分词: jogged 现在分词: jogging 第三人称单数: jogs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('damp', '[dæmp]', 'adj.潮湿的；有湿气的；沮丧的 n.湿气；潮湿 vt.使潮湿；使扫兴 vi.变潮湿', '1. Damp wood doesn\'t burn well. 潮湿的木头不好烧。 2. The building was cold and damp. 这房子又冷又湿。 3. The cheese molded in the damp cellar. 乳酪在潮湿的地下室中长了霉。 4. The party was a bit of a damp squib. 这次聚会有些扫兴。 5. The air of this room is impregnated with damp. 这房间充满着湿气。 6. Damp the cloth before you clean the windows. 在擦玻璃窗之前,把揩布弄湿。 7. Nothing could damp down my passion. 任何事情都不能磨灭我的激情。', '形容词: dampish 副词: damply 比较级: damper 最高级: dampest 名词: dampness 过去式: damped 过去分词: damped 现在分词: damping 第三人称单数: damps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ductile', '[\'dʌktaɪl]', 'adj.易延展的；柔软的；易教导的', '1. This metal is light and workable and ductile. 这种金属既轻，又易加工，延展性也好。 2. Artists use copper because it\'s one of the most ductile metals. 艺术家们使用铜作材料，是因为铜是延展性最好的金属之一。 3. Clay is ductile when it\'s mixed with water. 粘土和水混合，就变得柔软可塑。 4. Cadmium is a lustrous, silver-white, ductile, very malleable metal. 镉是一种有光泽的，银白色的，非常柔软的，延展性很好的金属。', '名词: ductility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inordinate', '[ɪn\'ɔːrdɪnət]', 'adj.过度的；非常的；无法无天的', '1. She had an inordinate fondness for junk food. 她喜欢吃零食到了无节制的程度。 2. They spent an inordinate amount of time and money on the production. 他们在生产上投入了过多的时间和资金。 3. The girl has inordinate passion for music. 这个女孩过分喜爱音乐。 4. A winner must be firm and posess strong stamina and inordinate courage. 成功者是需要坚韧的毅力和非凡的勇气的。', '副词: inordinately 名词: inordinacy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('steer', '[stɪr]', 'v.操纵；驾驶；掌舵；引导', '1. Sometimes an oar is used to steer a boat. 有时桨用以操纵小舟。 2. He steered the car skillfully through the narrow streets. 他熟练地驾驶着汽车穿过狭窄的街道。 3. People used to steer by the stars. 过去人们常常参照星星的方位来驾驶。 4. The old man settled himself to steer. 老人坐定下来掌舵。', '形容词: steerable 名词: steerer 过去式: steered 过去分词: steered 现在分词: steering 第三人称单数: steers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('labyrinth', '[\'læbərɪnθ]', 'n.迷宫；难解的事件', '1. The old building was a labyrinth of dark corridors. 那古老建筑是一座长廊纵横光线昏暗的迷宫。 2. The Labyrinth sport no longer exists. 迷宫运动不再存在。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('liberty', '[\'lɪbərti]', 'n.自由；自由权；冒失', '1. Those prisoners are dreaming of liberty. 这些囚犯们梦想着获得自由。 2. Everybody is at liberty to air his views. 每个人都有发表意见的自由。 3. Women used to have little liberty. 过去妇女没有多少自由。 4. I am afraid that I am not at liberty to discuss this matter. 对不起，我无权讨论这个问题。', '名词复数: liberties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delegate', '[\'delɪɡeɪt]', 'n.代表 v.派 ... 为代表；委派；授权；委托', '1. Babbitt was an official delegate. 巴比特是一名正式代表。 2. He was elected as a delegate to the annual conference. 他被选为年会代表。 3. He can\'t delegate command. 他不能委派代表来指挥。 4. You can\'t do all the jobs yourself---you can delegate a task to your subordinate. 你不能包揽所有的工作---你可以把任务委派给下属。', '名词: delegator 过去式: delegated 过去分词: delegated 现在分词: delegating 第三人称单数: delegates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compliment', '[\'kɑːmplɪmənt]', 'n.称赞；恭维；(复数)致意 vt.恭维；称赞', '1. I was embarrassed by their compliment. 对他们的称赞我感到很不安。 2. I feel greatly flattered at your compliment. 我对你的称赞感到受宠若惊。 3. They paid him a high compliment. 他们非常恭维他。 4. My compliments to your wife. 向您的夫人致意。 5. He complimented her on her new dress without even looking at it. 他连看都没看一眼，就称颂她的新衣服。', '过去式: complimented 过去分词: complimented 现在分词: complimenting 第三人称单数: compliments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('championship', '[\'tʃæmpiənʃɪp]', 'n.锦标赛；冠军；拥护', '1. How did the team prepare for the team championship? 你们的队伍是怎么准备这次锦标赛的？ 2. Her best moment was her first championship race. 她最棒的那一次比赛是她第一次参加锦标赛。 3. She made her mark by winning a championship. 她获得冠军，一举成名。 4. He gloried in his winning the championship. 他因获得冠军而洋洋得意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rattle', '[\'rætl]', 'vi.嘎嘎作响；喋喋不休 vt.使惊惶失措；使恼火；使作响；急促地谈讲 n.嘎嘎声；嘎嘎响的东西；拔浪鼓', '1. When the window blows,all the doors rattle. 只要风一吹,所有的门都吱吱嘎嘎作响。 2. The boy put some stones in a tin box and made them rattle. 男孩把一些石子放在铁盒子里，然后摇得哗啦哗啦地响。 3. The child rattled away merrily. 那孩子快活地喋喋不休地说着。 4. He rattled on about his job, not noticing how bored she was. 他只顾喋喋不休地说自己工作上的事，没注意到她有多麽腻烦。 5. It may, however, rattle the people you\'re meeting. 但是，它会使你要会见的人心慌意乱。 6. The rattle of the engine was very loud. 发动机的嘎嘎声很大。', '过去式: rattled 过去分词: rattled 现在分词: rattling 第三人称单数: rattles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repel', '[rɪ\'pel]', 'vt.排斥；抵制；击退；使反感 vi.排斥；反感', '1. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。 2. They stood prepared to repel any attack. 他们准备好打退一切进攻。 3. The crew repelled the attack. 船员击退了进攻。 4. A country must have the will to repel any invader. 一个国家得有决心击退任何入侵者。 5. The positive poles of two magnets repel each other. 两块磁铁的正极互相排斥。', '名词: repeller 过去式: repelled 过去分词: repelled 现在分词: repelling 第三人称单数: repels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aghast', '[ə\'ɡæst]', 'adj.惊骇的；吓呆的', '1. The robbers stood aghast at the sudden appearance of the policemen. 警察人员的突然出现，使那几个盗贼大惊失色。 2. Caderousse and his wife started and looked aghast at each other. 卡德鲁斯和他的妻子都吓了一跳，惊骇地互相望了一眼。 3. He stood aghast on hearing the news. 他听到这消息吓呆了。 4. She stood aghast at the black shadow in the drawing room. 她被客厅里的黑影吓呆了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disease', '[dɪ\'ziːz]', 'n.疾病 v.使…生病，感染', '1. The disease is still in its primary stage. 这疾病仍然在初发阶段。 2. The entire population was wiped out by the terrible disease. 所有的居民都被可怕的疾病夺去了生命。 3. The rapid spread of the disease is alarming the medical authorities. 这种疾病的迅速蔓延使医疗当局感到忧虑不安。 4. The treatment arrested the growth of the disease. 治疗抑制了病情的发展。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mottled', '[\'mɑːtld]', 'adj.有杂色的；斑驳的 动词mottle的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Mottled pink and brown areas are a combination of the cosmic dust and reddish emission from ionized hydrogen gas. 斑驳的粉红色和褐色区域是宇宙尘埃和电离氢气放射出的红光相结合的产物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squad', '[skwɑːd]', 'n.班；小队', '1. They are the precision shooting asset of a squad. 他们是步兵班里的神枪手。 2. The sergeant barked an order to his squad. 中士厉声向他班士兵下命令。 3. After a long drill he told the squad to fall out. 操练了好半天之后，他让这个班解散了。 4. As the rest of the squad wandered away, I remained at attention. 我们班的人都走了以后，我还在原地立正。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concise', '[kən\'saɪs]', 'adj.简明的；简要的', '1. His article is concise and comprehensive. 他的文章言简意赅。 2. I like the new concise dictionary very much. 我很喜欢这部新的简明词典。 3. I gave a concise answer to this. 我对于此事给了一个简要的答复。 4. He gave a concise and firm summary of our position. 他扼要而坚定地阐述了我方的立场。', '副词: concisely 名词: conciseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sluggish', '[\'slʌɡɪʃ]', 'adj.缓慢的；懒惰的；迟钝的；萧条的；无精打采的', '1. There is a sluggish stream. 那有一条流速缓慢的溪流。 2. The professor would try to awake their dormant and sluggish faculties. 这位教授应该试图唤醒他们沉睡和懒散的天赋。 3. This humid heat makes you feel rather sluggish. 这种湿热的天气使人感到懒洋洋的。 4. Some cities have been sluggish in their provision. 有些城市在作出规定方面行动迟缓。', '副词: sluggishly 名词: sluggishness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('benefactor', '[\'benɪfæktər]', 'n.恩人；捐助者；赠送者', '1. He did, however, discover his anonymous benefactor. 不过,他终于找到了那个匿名的恩人。 2. We showed high respect to benefactors. 我们对捐助者表达了崇高的敬意。 3. The quiet benefactor gets the largest reward. 这位不声张的捐助者得到了最大的回报。 4. The chieftain of that country is disguised as a benefactor this time. 那个国家的首领这一次伪装出一副施恩者的姿态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vibrate', '[\'vaɪbreɪt]', 'vt.(使)振动；(使)摇摆 vi.回响；颤动', '1. They will cause the speaker diaphragm to vibrate. 它们将引起扬声器薄膜振动。 2. Vibrating air makes your ear drums vibrate. 振动着的空气使你的耳鼓振动。 3. Vibrate,as of a swing before it comes to a total rest. 像秋千在平衡前的摇摆。 4. He saw the wings of her butterfly hairpin vibrate subtly. 姑娘头上的蝴蝶发夹微微颤动了一下翅膀。', '过去式: vibrated 过去分词: vibrated 现在分词: vibrating 第三人称单数: vibrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intercede', '[ˌɪntər\'siːd]', 'v.仲裁；说情；调解', '1. He was quickly snubbed when he tried to intercede. 当他试着说情时很快被制止了。 2. The governor promised to interced with the Home Office on behalf of the girl. 主管人员答应替那个女孩向内政部说情。 3. Farm and labor movements began to ask the government to intercede on their behalf. 农民和劳工运动开始要求政府代表他们出面调解。', '名词: interceder 过去式: interceded 过去分词: interceded 现在分词: interceding 第三人称单数: intercedes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('edible', '[\'edəbl]', 'adj.可食用的 n.食品；食物', '1. Is linseed oil edible? 亚麻籽油可以食用吗？ 2. Some of the algae are edible. 有些藻类是可以吃的。 3. Throw that tainted meat away; it\'s not edible. 把那块腐烂的肉扔掉，不能再吃了。 4. This food is scarcely edible. 这种食物真是难以下咽。 5. I eat everything that is edible. 我吃食品的每件事物。', '名词: edibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('groom', '[ɡruːm]', 'n.新郎；马夫；王室侍从者 v.打扮；梳理毛发；培养；准备（滑雪）赛道', '1. Her groom was much older than she was. 她的新郎比她大很多。 2. The bride and groom made a lovely couple. 新娘和新郎是天作之合的一对。 3. The groom returned to the carriage. 马夫回到马车那儿。 4. He groomed himself carefully for the party. 他为晚会仔细地打扮了一番。', '名词: groomer 过去式: groomed 过去分词: groomed 现在分词: grooming 第三人称单数: grooms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opponent', '[ə\'poʊnənt]', 'n.对手；反对者；敌手 adj.反对的；敌对的', '1. He was assailed by his political opponent. 他遭到政敌的攻击。 2. I tried to comfort him after he was defeated by his opponent. 他被对手击败后，我尽力安慰他。 3. He knocked down his opponent with a powerful left. 他一记有力的左手拳将对手击倒。 4. He is slashing wildly at his opponent with a sword. 他正用剑疯狂地朝对手乱砍。 5. The company, which had long been an opponent of electrification, changed its stance earlier this year in light of slipping global sales. 该公司长期以来一直反对的电气化，改变了其立场，在今年早些时候，鉴于全球销售下滑。', '名词: opponency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obstruct', '[əb\'strʌkt]', 'v.阻隔；妨碍；阻塞', '1. They do not obstruct most individuals who use patented products. 他们不会妨碍个人使用专利产品。 2. Five colors bewilder our eyes and obstruct our insights. 五种变化多端的颜色，迷惑我们的眼睛，妨碍我们的洞察力。 3. Such masses may also focally obstruct the biliary tract and lead to an elevated alkaline phosphatase. 肿物也可阻塞胆管，导致碱性磷酸酶升高。 4. But wherever Zhao went he would cause traffic jams and obstruct pavements as stunned crowds gathered to gawp. 但赵良所到之处，都会因惊讶的人们围观而造成塞车和道路阻塞。', '形容词: obstructive 副词: obstructively 名词: obstructer 过去式: obstructed 过去分词: obstructed 现在分词: obstructing 第三人称单数: obstructs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subvert', '[səb\'vɜːrt]', 'vt.推翻；颠覆；毁灭；使败坏', '1. The rebellious troops attempted to subvert the present government. 叛军曾企图推翻现政府。 2. He intended to subvert lawful government in his country. 他阴谋颠覆自己国家的合法政府。 3. This doctrine would subvert the very foundation of all written constitutions 这种论说将使一切成文宪法的根本基础遭到破坏。 4. Democracy can easily be subverted from within. 民主政体容易自内部加以破坏。', '名词: subverter 过去式: subverted 过去分词: subverted 现在分词: subverting 第三人称单数: subverts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trap', '[træp]', 'n.圈套；陷阱；困境；双轮轻便马车；U（或S）型管道；防臭瓣 v.设圈套；陷入（困境）', '1. The police set a trap to catch the thief. 警察设下了捉拿窃贼的圈套。 2. The only thing the wolf could do was climbing up to the ground from the trap. 那只狼惟一能做的就是从陷阱里爬到地面上来。 3. To break out of the poverty trap they need help from the government. 为了摆脱贫困的处境，他们需要政府的帮助。 4. She didn\'t say anything about a trap. 她根本没提马车的事。 5. By clever questioning they trapped him into making a confession. 他们用巧妙的提问诱使他招认了。', '过去式: trapped 过去分词: trapped 现在分词: trapping 第三人称单数: traps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dedication', '[ˌdedɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.奉献；献词；献堂礼', '1. Her dedication to her work was admirable. 她对工作的奉献精神可钦可佩。 2. She wanted to buy his love with her dedication to him and his work. 她想通过自己对他及其工作的奉献来换取他的爱。 3. His talent and dedication will insure his success. 他的才气和执着将确保他成功。 4. The book\'s dedication reads \"To Mother\". 本书献词写道：“献给母亲”。', '形容词: dedicative');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anecdote', '[\'ænɪkdoʊt]', 'n.轶事；奇闻', '1. He departs from the text to tell an anecdote. 他没讲课文而讲了一段轶事。 2. He preceded his lecture with a humorous anecdote. 他以一个幽默的轶事开始他的演说 3. He told me some anecdotes about our English teacher. 他告诉我几个关于英语老师的掌故。 4. It had never been more than a family anecdote. 那不过是个家庭趣谈罢了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sicken', '[\'sɪkən]', 'v.患病；生病；恶心；使厌倦', '1. The plants and flowers sicken in the autumn. 在秋天花草都枯萎了。 2. However, sometimes the virus can sicken humans. 但是有时病毒可以使人患病。 3. The child sickened with whooping cough. 那孩子得了百日咳。 4. The animal began to sicken and soon died. 那动物开始生病，不久就死了。', '名词: sickener 过去式: sickened 过去分词: sickened 现在分词: sickening 第三人称单数: sickens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('designing', '[dɪ\'zaɪnɪŋ]', 'adj.狡猾的；有预谋的 n.设计 动词design的现在分词.', '1. She was a designing young person. 她是个工于心计的年轻女子。 2. Designing colleagues stopped them from promoting me. 有些别有用心的同事阻止他们提拔我. 3. Correct designing comes from practice. 正确的设计来自实践。', '副词: designingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interact', '[ˌɪntər\'ækt]', 'vi.相互作用；相互联系；相互影响；互动', '1. These factors interact intimately and cannot be separated. 这些因素相互之间紧密联系，不能分开。 2. Mother and baby interact in a very complex way. 母亲与婴儿以非常复杂的方式相互影响。 3. Economists also study how people interact with one another. 经济学家也研究人们之间的相互影响。 4. Teachers should interact with students more frequently in the class. 老师应该在课堂上与学生有更多的互动。', '过去式: interacted 过去分词: interacted 现在分词: interacting 第三人称单数: interacts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anatomy', '[ə\'nætəmi]', 'n.解剖学；解剖学专著；分解；解剖；骨骸', '1. The anatomy of the strands was not investigated. 没人研究过菌绳的解剖学。 2. We don\'t get to onto anatomy until next year. 我们明年才能学到解剖学。 3. Various parts of his anatomy were clearly visible. 他身体的各个部分都看得很清楚。 4. Do you remember the lesson on the anatomy of a frog? 你还记得我们解剖青蛙的那堂课吗？', '名词复数: anatomies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vertebrate', '[\'vɜːrtɪbrət]', 'adj.脊椎的；脊椎动物的 n.脊椎动物', '1. A dog is a vertebrate animal. 狗是脊椎动物。 2. So far it has not been detected in a vertebrate animal. 到目前为止，脊椎动物体内还没有发现过。 3. The organ in invertebrates is similar to the vertebrate liver. 无脊椎动物体内该器官与脊椎动物的肝脏相似。 4. Fish, birds and human beings are all vertebrates. 鱼、鸟和人类都是脊椎动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('provoke', '[prə\'voʊk]', 'vt.激怒；惹起；驱使', '1. If you provoke the dog, he may bite you. 你如果激怒了这条狗，它可能会咬你。 2. Don\'t provoke the animals in the cage. 不要激怒笼中的动物。 3. His rudeness provoked me to strike him. 他的粗鲁惹得我揍了他。 4. Such a questionable assertion is sure to provoke criticism. 这种有问题的主张肯定会招致非议。', '副词: provokingly 过去式: provoked 过去分词: provoked 现在分词: provoking 第三人称单数: provokes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slant', '[slænt]', 'n.倾斜；斜面；个人的观点或见解；倾向性；偏见 vt.使倾斜；歪曲 vi.倾斜', '1. The wooden floor has a noticeable slant. 这木地板可以看得出有些倾斜。 2. Has your roof a sharp slant? 你的屋顶是否有一个陡峭的斜面？ 3. She put a new slant on the play. 她对那出戏提出了一种新的见解。 4. The editorial had an antiunion slant. 这篇社论有一种反工会的倾向。 5. When drawing, shearing means to slant an image. 绘制时,修剪意味着使图像倾斜。 6. Most handwriting slants to the right. 大多数手写体都向右斜。', '副词: slantingly 过去式: slanted 过去分词: slanted 现在分词: slanting 第三人称单数: slants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('luxurious', '[lʌɡ\'ʒʊriəs]', 'adj.奢侈的；豪华的', '1. She has been honing for a luxurious life. 她一直渴望过豪华奢侈的生活。 2. He lived in luxurious surroundings. 他生活在奢侈的环境中。 3. The lady appeared with a luxurious fur coat. 那位夫人穿着华贵的毛皮外套来了。 4. The millionaire leads a luxurious life. 那个百万富翁过着豪华的生活。', '副词: luxuriously 名词: luxuriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gallant', '[\'ɡælənt]', 'adj.英勇的；(男子对女子)殷勤的；华丽的；雄伟的 n.时髦男士；对女子殷勤的男士；求爱者 v.献殷勤', '1. These gallant soldiers will protect our country. 这些勇敢的士兵会保卫我们的国家的。 2. He was very gallant at the ball. 他在舞会上对妇女大献殷勤。 3. Her poverty had been a venial fault for two gallant gentlemen. 她的贫穷对那两位殷勤的绅士而言，只是一个微不足道的缺点。 4. The garden was made gallant with tulips. 花园里种著郁金香显得气派不凡。 5. When he puts on his best clothes he certainly looks like a gallant. 他穿上最好的衣服时，当然像个时髦人物了。', '副词: gallantly 过去式: gallanted 过去分词: gallanted 现在分词: gallanting 第三人称单数: gallants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('latent', '[\'leɪtnt]', 'adj.潜伏的；潜在的', '1. He was infected with a latent infection. 他被感染了一种潜伏性的传染病。 2. We must take measures to control the latent disease germs. 我们必须采取措施控制潜伏的病菌。 3. Within everyone there was a latent volcano of unhappiness and discontent. 在每个人心中都有一座潜伏着不幸福与不满的火山。 4. The latent cause of crime is often avarice. 贫婪常是犯罪的潜在诱因。', '副词: latently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relieved', '[rɪ\'liːvd]', 'adj.放心的；放松的 动词relieve的过去式和过去分词.', '1. She looked immensely relieved when she heard the news. 她一听到这个消息似乎立刻放心了。 2. They exchanged relieved glances. 他们如释重负地彼此看了看。 3. She had a relieved look on her face. 她脸上现出宽慰的表情。 4. The thief relieved him of his wallet. 那小偷把他的钱包偷走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('owl', '[aʊl]', 'n.猫头鹰', '1. The owl swooped down on the mouse. 那只猫头鹰向着老鼠猛扑下来。 2. The owl hunts while you repose in bed. 你躺在床上安然入睡时，猫头鹰却要去觅食。 3. The hooting of an owl broke the silence now and again, giving Linda the creeps. 猫头鹰的叫声不时打破寂静，使琳达心惊肉跳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bashful', '[\'bæʃfl]', 'adj.害羞的；羞怯的；羞愧的', '1. The bashful boy was nervous with strangers. 那个害羞的小男孩遇到陌生人就紧张。 2. He suddenly became bashful the minute the girl he liked showed up. 那个他喜欢的女生一出现他就变得非常害羞。 3. She is bashful about speaking in public. 她在公开场合讲话会羞怯。 4. Out with it. Don\'t be affectedly bashful. 有话快说，别扭扭捏捏的。', '副词: bashfully 名词: bashfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('substantial', '[səb\'stænʃl]', 'adj.大量的；坚固的；实质的；可观的 n.本质；重要部份', '1. New economic development policies led to substantial and rapid growth. 新的经济发展政策带来了快速和大量的增长。 2. Those workers have built many substantial buildings in the recent years. 近几年那些工人建造了许多坚固的建筑。 3. The reforms have made substantial headway. 改革取得了实质的进展。 4. The article is devoid of substantial matter. 这篇文章缺乏实质性的内容。', '副词: substantially 名词: substantiality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slander', '[\'slændər]', 'n.中伤；诽谤 vt.中伤；诽谤', '1. In the last election, they spattered their rivals with slander 在上届选举中,他们用谣言中伤对手。 2. I gave my ear to what I now know was the malice of slander . 我过去听信了谣言，现在我知道那是恶意中伤。 3. It\'s a malignant slander to me. 这对我是恶意的诽谤。 4. Her company is suing her for slander because of her remarks about their safety record. 由于她发表了关于公司安全记录的言论，该公司正以诽谤罪起诉她。 5. Brothers, do not slander one another. 弟兄们，你们不可彼此批评。', '形容词: slanderous 副词: slanderously 名词: slanderer 过去式: slandered 过去分词: slandered 现在分词: slandering 第三人称单数: slanders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enthusiasm', '[ɪn\'θuːziæzəm]', 'n.热情；热心；热衷的事物', '1. His refusal iced our enthusiasm. 他的拒绝浇熄了我们的热情。 2. She seemed lacking in enthusiasm when we were talking about that film. 我们谈论那部电影时,她看来好像没多大热情。 3. His enthusiasm made everyone else interested. 他的热心激发了大家的兴致。 4. One of my great enthusiasms is music. 我的一大爱好就是音乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inborn', '[ˌɪn\'bɔːrn]', 'adj.天生的；生来的', '1. Confidence is built, not inborn. 信心是建立起来的，不是天生的。 2. A woman is an inborn guardian of \"home\". 一个女人天生就是一个“家”的守候者。 3. Birds have an inborn ability to fly. 鸟生来就会飞。 4. He has a certain inborn genius that can\'t be taught or learned. 他具有的一些与生俱来的天才我永远无法通过教或者学去获得。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('burgeon', '[\'bɜːrdʒən]', 'v.发芽；萌芽；迅速发展 n.芽；嫩枝', '1. Seeds begin to burgeon at the commencement of spring. 春天来临时种子开始发芽。 2. In these days the oaks shall burn in the forest glades, and acorns shall burgeon on the lime trees\' boughs. 在那些日子里，橡树会在林间空地里燃烧，橡子会在酸橙树的主枝上萌芽。 3. She burgeoned into a fine actress. 她迅速成长为一名优秀的女演员。 4. We hope that the festival will burgeon out slowly but steadily. 我们希望这欢乐的日子将逐步稳定的发展下去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('engrossed', '[ɪn\'ɡroʊst]', 'adj.全神贯注的 动词engross的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. He was so engrossed in his work that he forgot to eat. 他全神贯注地工作，连吃饭也忘了。 2. Newton was so engrossed in his laboratory work that he often forgot to eat. ＂牛顿全神贯注地在实验室工作，常常连吃饭也忘了。＂ 3. She was engrossed in painting. 她全神贯注于绘画。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adobe', '[ə\'doʊbi]', 'n.泥砖；土坯；泥砖建筑物；制砖粘土 Adobe. n.美国奥多比电脑软件公司', '1. The villagers built their houses with adobe. 村民们用晒乾的泥砖造房子。 2. This way the adobe can be shaped into bricks of the desired size. 用这种方法，泥砖土就能被塑成所需尺寸的砖。 3. But people who work with adobe must experiment. 但是从事土坯工作的人必须做试验。 4. Adobe is soil that contains at least forty percent clay. 土坯是包含至少百分之四十粘土的土壤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('respective', '[rɪ\'spektɪv]', 'adj.分别的；各自的', '1. He drove them both to their respective homes. 他驾车把他们分别送到家里。 2. The three men were given work according to their respective abilities. 这三个人根据各自的能力被分配了工作。 3. Product name is trademark or registered trademark of their respective owner. 产品名称为它们各自所有者的商标或注册商标。', '名词: respectiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('supple', '[\'sʌpl]', 'adj.柔软的；逢迎的；灵活的 vt.使柔软；使柔顺 vi.变柔软；变柔顺', '1. I picture my spine supple and flexible. 我想像我的脊椎是柔软弹性的。 2. The leather I tanned is supple and durable. 我鞣制的皮革特别柔韧耐用。 3. Exercise keeps you supple. 经常锻炼可使身体灵活。 4. She has a supple mind. 她头脑灵活。 5. It had simply made her sympathetic and supple. 它只是使她变得随和柔顺而已。', '副词: supply 比较级: suppler 最高级: supplest 名词: suppleness 过去式: suppled 过去分词: suppled 现在分词: suppling 第三人称单数: supples');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tunnel', '[\'tʌnl]', 'n.隧道；地道；洞穴 v.挖地道；挖隧道', '1. The heavy traffic crawled through the narrow tunnel. 拥挤的车辆慢吞吞地穿过狭窄的隧道。 2. Suddenly the train roared into a tunnel and everything was black. 突然火车轰隆隆地驶入一个隧道，四周的一切都漆黑一团。 3. The kid dug a tunnel in the sand. 小孩在沙堆里挖了一个地道。 4. Moles make underground tunnels. 鼹鼠常打地洞。 5. The engineers had to tunnel through solid rock. 工程师须要在坚实的岩石中开凿隧道。', '名词: tunneler 过去式: tunneled/tunnelled 过去分词: tunneled/tunnelled 现在分词: tunneling/tunnelling 第三人称单数: tunnels/tunnels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('desert', '[\'dezərt]', 'n.沙漠；荒地；应得(的惩罚或奖励) v.遗弃；离弃；放弃；擅离职守', '1. Two thirds of the country is dry or desert. 这个国家有三分之二的地方气候干燥,或者是沙漠。 2. Some of them died of thirst in the desert. 他们中有些人在沙漠中渴死了。 3. Water can transform a desert into a garden. 水能把一片不毛之地变成一座花园。 4. The baby\'s mother deserted him soon after giving birth. 那个母亲生下他后不久就把他遗弃了。', '名词: deserter 过去式: deserted 过去分词: deserted 现在分词: deserting 第三人称单数: deserts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dense', '[dens]', 'adj.密集的；稠密的；浓密的', '1. My hometown is a large city with a dense population. :我的家乡是个人口密集的大城市。 2. Books with dense print can be difficult to read. 印得密密麻麻的书阅读起来很困难。 3. A dense mass of black hair framed his face. 浓密的黑发衬托着他的面庞。 4. They hewed their way through the dense jungle. 他们在浓密的丛林里开辟出一条路来。', '副词: densely 比较级: denser 最高级: densest 名词: denseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stringent', '[\'strɪndʒənt]', 'adj.严格的；银根紧的；紧迫的', '1. Licences are only granted under the most stringent conditions. 只有符合极其严格的条件才颁发许可证。 2. People began verify their scientific hypotheses by stringent tests. 人们开始用精确的试验证实自己的科学假说。 3. Some of our most outstanding buildings have been created on a stringent budget. 我们的一些杰出作品往往是在很紧凑的预算下设计建成的。 4. Based on above analysis the stringent problems needed to resolve are put forward. 在此基础上指出今后迫切需要解决的问题。', '副词: stringently 名词: stringency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stripe', '[straɪp]', 'n.条纹；条纹布；种类；军士军阶 n.鞭打；抽打 vt.使 ... 带有条纹', '1. I need one without stripe, please. 我需要没有条纹的。 2. The entire body of a zebra is marked with black and whitish stripe. 斑马的全身都有黑白条纹。 3. Which do you want for your new dress, a stripe or a check? 你要哪种料子来做新连衣裙，条子的还是方格的? 4. \"All Fascists are not of one mind, one stripe\" (Lillian Hellman) 所有的法西斯主义者并非一个思想,一个种类。', '过去式: striped 过去分词: striped 现在分词: striping 第三人称单数: stripes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alter', '[\'ɔːltər]', 'v.改变；更改；阉割；切除卵巢', '1. But nothing can alter the facts. 但任何东西也改变不了这些事实。 2. Alter Current Boot Record Serial Number. 更改当前引导纪录序列号。 3. Marshaling the structure can transform the layout and alter the offset. 封送结构可转换布局并更改偏移量。', '过去式: altered 过去分词: altered 现在分词: altering 第三人称单数: alters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cape', '[keɪp]', 'n.岬；海角 n.披肩', '1. Rudolf was rounding a bleak, dangerous cape. 鲁道夫正在绕过一个荒凉险峻的海岬。 2. The cape extends far into the ocean. 那海岬伸向海洋远处。 3. My favorite movie is Cape No. 7. 我最喜欢的电影是”海角七号”。 4. The man has a red cape. 这人有一件红色的斗篷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accommodate', '[ə\'kɑːmədeɪt]', 'vt.供给住宿；使适应；容纳；提供；顾及；调解 vi.适应；调节', '1. This hotel can accommodate up to 500 guests. 这旅馆可供500位来宾住宿。 2. We must accommodate ourselves to circumstances. 我们必须适应环境。 3. One flat can accommodate a family of five. 一套单元房可容纳一个五口之家。 4. The bank is accommodating its customers more than it used to. 这家银行现在给客户贷款比以前多了。 5. Her eyes took a while to accommodate to the darkness. 过了一会儿，她的眼睛才能适应黑暗。', '形容词: accommodative 名词: accommodativeness 过去式: accommodated 过去分词: accommodated 现在分词: accommodating 第三人称单数: accommodates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('signify', '[\'sɪɡnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.表示；预示；意味着；象征 vi.有重要性', '1. She signifies her disagreement. 她表示她不同意。 2. Do dark clouds signify rain? 有乌云是否显示要下雨? 3. A red sunset signifies fine weather. 红红的晚霞是晴天的预兆。 4. A fever usually signifies that there is something wrong with the body. 发烧通常意味着身体有点毛病。 5. It doesn\'t signify, so you needn\'t worry about it. 这无所谓，你不必担心。', '形容词: signifiable 名词: signifier 过去式: signified 过去分词: signified 现在分词: signifying 第三人称单数: signifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strap', '[stræp]', 'n.皮带；带子 vt.(用带子)捆扎；(用带子)抽打', '1. The strap had been fretted away. 皮带已经被磨损了。 2. Her camera strap has broken. 她的照相机吊带断了。 3. A safety strap is used to prevent falling. 安全带是用来防止滑落的。 4. A watch strap holds a watch on your wrist. 表带把手表系在手腕上。 5. Experienced travelers strap in without waiting to be asked. 有经验的旅客一就座便自动系好安全带。', '过去式: strapped 过去分词: strapped 现在分词: strapping 第三人称单数: straps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nuclear', '[\'nuːkliər]', 'adj.原子核的；原子能的；核心的', '1. Nuclear binding energies are strikingly high. 原子核的结合能是极大的。 2. The college students are active to crusade against the nuclear weapons. 大学生们积极投入开展反对核武器的运 动。 3. They decided to establish a nuclear power station. 他们决定修建一所核电站。 4. A nuclear family consists of parents and their children only. 核心家庭一般只有父母和孩子两代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conversation', '[ˌkɑːnvər\'seɪʃn]', 'n.谈话；会话', '1. I listened to their conversation. 我倾听他们的谈话。 2. Did you have a conversation with him? 你和他谈过话了吗？ 3. The band drowned our conversation. 乐队的演奏声把我们谈话的声音淹没了。 4. His French has come on a lot since he joined the conversation class. 他自从参加了会话班，法语取得了很大进步。', '形容词: conversational 副词: conversationally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enterprising', '[\'entərpraɪzɪŋ]', 'adj.有事业心的；有进取心的；有魄力的', '1. She may not have be the clever candidate but she is certainly the most enterprising 她就算不是最聪明的候选人, 也肯定是最有事业心的 2. The enterprising children opened a lemonade stand. 一些有进取心的孩子摆摊卖柠檬汽水。 3. The condition of the postwar years brought many enterprising men to the fore. 战后这些年来的情况使许多有进取心的人成为名人。 4. Some enterprising girls organized a sponsored walk. 几个有魄力的女子筹办了一项慈善步行活动。', '副词: enterprisingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prone', '[proʊn]', 'adj.易于 ... 的；有 ... 倾向的；俯卧的', '1. He was prone to anger. 他易于发怒。 2. The child is rather accident-prone. 那个小孩很容易出事儿。 3. People are more prone to make mistakes when they are tired. 人们疲劳时更容易出差错。 4. He\'s probably prone to domestic violence. 他也许有家庭暴力的倾向。', '副词: pronely 名词: proneness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('daring', '[\'derɪŋ]', 'adj.勇敢的；大胆的 n.勇敢；勇气', '1. He had proved himself a most daring airman. 他已证明自己是个极其勇敢的飞行员。 2. The daring exploits of the parachutists were much admired. 跳伞者大胆的冒险动作令人赞叹不已。 3. She said some daring things. 她说了一些大胆的话。 4. He was a soldier famous for his daring. 他是个以勇敢出名的战士。', '副词: daringly 名词: daringness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blessed', '[\'blesɪd]', 'adj.神圣的；有福的；愉快的；<口>该死的 动词bless的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Blessed are the humble. 谦虚的人有福了。 2. They lived their lives in blessed calmness. 他们过着幸福宁静的日子。 3. I hope you all have a blessed day. 希望你们都拥有幸福的每一天。 4. I can\'t see a blessed thing without my glasses. 我不带眼镜他妈的什么也看不清。 5. The Pope blessed the crowd. 教皇向人群祝福。', '副词: blessedly 异体字: blest 名词: blessedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crusade', '[kruː\'seɪd]', 'n.改革运动 vi.参与斗争或运动 Crusade. n.十字军东征', '1. It\'s a crusade against corruption. 这是一场反腐败的运动。 2. He was deeply involved with the anti-drugs crusade. 他深深地涉入了反毒品运动。 3. The college students are active to crusade against the nuclear weapons. 大学生们积极投入开展反对核武器的运 动。 4. We must crusade for world peace. 我们必须为世界和平而奋斗。 5. In the first real crusade Jerusalem was captured. 第一次真正的十字军东征时攻下了耶路撒冷。', '名词: crusader 过去式: crusaded 过去分词: crusaded 现在分词: crusading 第三人称单数: crusades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diversification', '[daɪˌvɜːsɪfɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.多元化', '1. We encourage diversification in the school system. 我们鼓励办学模式有多元代的发展。 2. Market diversification is an inevitable trend. 市场多元化是一个不可逆转的趋势。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oxygen', '[\'ɑːksɪdʒən]', 'n.氧；氧气', '1. Water contains hydrogen and oxygen. 水含有氢和氧。 2. Hydrogen and oxygen are gases. 氢和氧是气体。 3. Plants can absorb carbon dioxide and release oxygen. 植物可以吸收二氧化碳释放氧气。 4. Mars is too dry and poor in oxygen. 火星上面过于干燥，并且缺乏氧气。', '形容词: oxygenic 副词: oxygenically 简写符号: O');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flounder', '[\'flaʊndər]', 'v.挣扎；踌躇；笨拙而错乱地说或做 n.挣扎；错乱的行动 n.比目鱼；鲽', '1. His flounder in pain and sufferings dying. 他挣扎着在痛苦中死去。 2. They have to flounder in a morassof contradictions. 他们不得不在矛盾重重的困境中挣扎。 3. She could only flounder in the water. 她只能慌乱地在水里挣扎。 4. They have to flounder in a morassof contradictions. 他们不得不在矛盾重重的困境中挣扎。 5. I consider a flounder to be flat. 我以为比目鱼是扁平的。', '名词复数: flounder 过去式: floundered 过去分词: floundered 现在分词: floundering 第三人称单数: flounders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sarcastic', '[sɑːr\'kæstɪk]', 'adj.讽刺的', '1. He chopped in with a sarcastic remark. 他突然插进一句讽刺的话。 2. I felt completely squashed by her sarcastic comment. 她冷嘲热讽把我噎得一句话都说不出来。 3. I could see from her expression that his sarcastic comments had hit home. 从她的表情中我可以看出他那些挖苦人的话已经触及她的痛处。', '副词: sarcastically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('narrate', '[nə\'reɪt]', 'v.叙述；给（电视或电影）作旁白', '1. Shall I narrate a strange experience of mine? 我把我的一次奇遇叙述一下好吗？ 2. As he continued to narrate his story I could hardly bear to listen. 他继续叙述他的故事，我几乎不忍心听下去。', '形容词: narratable 名词: narratability 过去式: narrated 过去分词: narrated 现在分词: narrating 第三人称单数: narrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apex', '[\'eɪpeks]', 'n.顶点；最高点；尖端', '1. The apex of the greater tuberosity was determined by placing a marker on the superiormost area of the greater tuberosity. 在大结节的上级放置一个标记以确定大结节的顶点。 2. As I neared the apex of the turn, a big pickup truck came around in my side of the road. 当我接近顶点的又一个大卡车来到我身边周围的道路。 3. So Andrew began to diversify, creating the Apex Security division and a videography service. 于是，安德鲁开始多元发展，创设了尖端通讯保险部门以及一项电视录象制作的服务。', '名词复数: apexes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extensive', '[ɪk\'stensɪv]', 'adj.广泛的；广阔的；广大的；大量的', '1. The device had undergone extensive testing. 这种装置经受过广泛的试验。 2. I have benefited a lot from extensive reading. 广泛的阅读使我受益匪浅。 3. The teacher had both extensive knowledge and profound scholarship. 先生的学问博大精深。 4. The mansion has extensive grounds. 这大厦四周的庭园广阔。', '副词: extensively 名词: extensiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diffuse', '[dɪ\'fjuːz]', 'vt.扩散；散开；传播 vi.弥漫；扩散 adj.冗长的；四散的', '1. The problem is how to diffuse power without creating anarchy. 问题在于如何将权力分散而不造成无政府状态。 2. Fashion trends diffuse themselves rapidly around the globe. 时装新潮很快就在全世界流行起来。 3. The roses diffuse the scent to the air miles around. 玫瑰花的香味儿弥漫在几英里的空气中。 4. He resolved to diffuse the special knowledge that he possessed. 他决心要传播他所具有的特别的知识。 5. Around the cluster is a huge vague diffuse nebulae. 围绕该星团的是一个巨大的模糊的弥漫星云。 6. Professor Smith cut off their diffuse speech and agreed to help them. 史密斯教授打断他们冗长的演讲,答应帮助他们。', '副词: diffusely 名词: diffuseness 过去式: diffused 过去分词: diffused 现在分词: diffusing 第三人称单数: diffuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ruin', '[\'ruːɪn]', 'vt.毁灭；毁坏；（使）破产；糟蹋，使（妇女）失去贞操 n.毁灭；废墟；崩溃', '1. He ruined his prospects by carelessness. 他因疏忽大意而断送了前途。 2. The politics of the company will ruin their image. 公司的策略会毁掉他们的形象。 3. His enemies maliciously conspired to ruin him. 他的敌人恶毒地密谋搞垮他。 4. The rain ruined my painting. 这场雨把我的画给毁了。 5. His rashness led ultimately to his ruin. 他的急躁鲁莽最终导致了他的毁灭。', '形容词: ruinable 名词: ruiner 过去式: ruined 过去分词: ruined 现在分词: ruining 第三人称单数: ruins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seismic', '[\'saɪzmɪk]', 'adj.地震的', '1. Most materials have different seismic properties. 大多数物质都具有不同的地震的特性。 2. This earthquake measured 7 according to the seismic survey. 经测定，这次地震的烈度为七级。', '副词: seismically 名词: seismicity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('depot', '[\'diːpoʊ]', 'n.贮藏所；仓库；车站；补给站', '1. The ammunition depot is heavily guarded. 弹药库戒备森严。 2. The guerrillas burned down the enemy\'s depot. 游击队放火烧了敌人的仓库。 3. They leased the building as a depot. 他们租用这栋大楼作仓库。 4. Rhett was waiting for her at the depot with the carriage. 瑞德带着一辆马车在车站等候她。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impatient', '[ɪm\'peɪʃnt]', 'adj.不耐烦的；急躁的', '1. He tends to snap at people when he gets impatient. 他一不耐烦的时候就对人没有好声气。 2. The impatient teacher slapped the student. 这位不耐烦的老师掌击了学生。 3. Your impatient self clearly suffers from a similar fixed cost of carrying out subtraction. 你身上那个急躁的自我，显然在实施减法时承受着类似的固定成本。', '副词: impatiently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('provide', '[prə\'vaɪd]', 'v.供给；提供；准备；规定；抚养', '1. Sheep provide us with wool. 羊供给我们羊毛。 2. The hotel provides a reservation of tickets for its residents. 这家旅馆为旅客提供订票服务。 3. We have to provide for possible accidents. 我们要为可能发生的意外作些准备。 4. The law provides that these ancient buildings must be preserved. 法律规定，这些古老的建筑应该保存。', '过去式: provided 过去分词: provided 现在分词: providing 第三人称单数: provides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('momentous', '[moʊ\'mentəs]', 'adj.重要的；重大的', '1. I have some momentous news to tell you. 我有重要的消息要告诉你。 2. I am deeply honoured to be invited to this momentous occasion. 能应邀出席如此重要的场合，我深感荣幸。 3. This is a momentous, hard-won achievement. 这是一个非常重大和来之不易的成就。 4. History bears evidence that each momentous political change is usually followed by an economic revival. 历史证明，在每次重大的政治变革之后随之而来的往往是经济上的复兴。', '副词: momentously 名词: momentousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('session', '[\'seʃn]', 'n.会议；会期；开庭期；学期；一段时间', '1. If the negotiations between the rich northerly nations and poor southerly nations make headway, it is intended that a ministerial session in December should be arranged. 要是北方富国和南方穷国之间的谈判获得进展的话,就打算在十二月份安排召开部长级的会议。 2. Several bills were enacted at the end of this session of Parliament. 这届国会结束时，好几个议案制定成为法律。 3. Is Parliament in session during the summer? 议会在夏季是开会期吗? 4. Be seated! This court is now in session. 请坐下！本庭现在开庭。', '形容词: sessional 副词: sessionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convict', '[kən\'vɪkt]', 'vt.宣判 ... 有罪；使 ... 知罪 n.囚犯；罪犯 adj.被定罪的', '1. You can\'t convict a man of a crime on circumstantial evidence alone. 不能只靠旁证就判定一个人有罪。 2. The criminal was convicted of murder. 歹徒被判谋杀罪。 3. He was convicted of his errors. 他认识到自己所犯的过失。 4. The convict fled away with a hostage. 囚犯带着一个人质跑了。 5. Let a convict person go free without any punishment. 让被定罪的人自由，不进行任何惩罚。', '过去式: convicted 过去分词: convicted 现在分词: convicting 第三人称单数: convicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glean', '[ɡliːn]', 'v.拾落穗；收集', '1. What useful thing can you glean from that? 哪些有益的事情你能收集到的？ 2. He likes to glean the bamboo telegraph. 他喜欢收集小道消息。', '名词: gleaner 过去式: gleaned 过去分词: gleaned 现在分词: gleaning 第三人称单数: gleans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overdue', '[ˌoʊvər\'duː]', 'adj.过期的；未兑的；迟到的', '1. Now they are overdue and I shall have to pay a fine. 现在它们过期了,我不得不付罚款。 2. The library called in all overdue books. 图书馆要求把所有逾期未还的书收回。 3. Payment is now four days overdue. 付款期已超过四天了。 4. Your payment is 6 months overdue in total. 贵公司的应付款项总计已过期6个月。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insulate', '[\'ɪnsəleɪt]', 'vt.使绝缘；隔离', '1. We can insulate a live wire with rubber. 我们可用橡胶使带电的电线绝缘。 2. Rubber is used to insulate electric wires. 橡胶被用来使电线与外界绝缘。 3. Her parents tried to insulate her from dangerous influences. 她的父母试图把她与危险的影响隔绝。 4. It is important to insulate the furnace from any neighbouring woodwork with brick and asbestos. 用砖和石棉把炉子与周围所有的木制品隔开，这很重要。', '过去式: insulated 过去分词: insulated 现在分词: insulating 第三人称单数: insulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foul', '[faʊl]', 'adj.恶臭的；邪恶的；污秽的；恶劣的；犯规的 n.犯规 v.弄脏；妨碍；犯规', '1. He opened the window to let out the foul air. 他打开窗户，放出污浊的空气。 2. The foul weather spoiled our vacation. 恶劣的天气把我们的假期糟踏了。 3. She has a foul temper. 她脾气暴躁。 4. The ball was foul. 这球犯规了。 5. The forward made a foul in the penalty area. 前锋在禁区内犯规了。 6. Owners who allow their dogs to foul the footpath will be fined. 主人若放任狗弄脏人行道将受处罚。', '副词: foully 比较级: fouler 最高级: foulest 名词: foulness 过去式: fouled 过去分词: fouled 现在分词: fouling 第三人称单数: fouls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fatalism', '[\'feɪtəlɪzəm]', 'n.宿命论', '1. It is very easy to confuse hard-determinism with fatalism . 很容易将刚性决定论与宿命论混淆起来。 2. The historicist view of social development does not imply fatalism. 历史决定论关于社会发展的观点并不意味着宿命论。', '形容词: fatalistic 副词: fatalistically 名词: fatalist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tempt', '[tempt]', 'vt.诱惑；怂恿；引诱；吸引', '1. The warm weather tempted us into going for a swim. 暖和的天气诱使我们去游泳。 2. I ought not to have let you tempt me into asking you a rude question. 我本来就不应该让你怂恿我跟你提出一个无礼的问题。 3. Those advertisements try to tempt people into buying their products. 那些广告试图怂恿大家去购买其产品。 4. He was tempted into making a false step. 他被引诱做了一件傻事。', '形容词: temptable 名词: tempter 过去式: tempted 过去分词: tempted 现在分词: tempting 第三人称单数: tempts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fortunate', '[\'fɔːrtʃənət]', 'adj.幸运的；侥幸的；带来幸运的', '1. It\'s fortunate you didn\'t forget. 幸好你没忘。 2. The girl was fortunate enough to have her mother as a bosom friend. 这个女孩非常幸运，她的妈妈是她的知心朋友。 3. The couple forfeited their independence in order to help those less fortunate. 这对夫妇把富裕出的钱都拿出来帮助那些受难的人。 4. It is fortunate that the tanker did not leak. 庆幸的是，油罐车没有发生泄漏。', '副词: fortunately 名词: fortunateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dialogue', '[\'daɪəlɑːɡ]', 'n.对话 v.对话', '1. The novel contains more narrative than dialogue. 这部小说里的叙述比对话多。 2. The writer is not very good at writing dialogues. 这个作家不太擅长写对白。 3. At last there can be a reasonable dialogue between our two governments. 我们两国最后终于能理智地进行对话了。 4. They dialogue for three hours failed to come to an agreement. 他们谈了三个小时，没有达成一致。', '异体字: dialog 名词: dialoguer 过去式: dialogued/dialoged 过去分词: dialogued/dialoged 现在分词: dialoguing/dialoging 第三人称单数: dialogues/dialogs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('additional', '[ə\'dɪʃənl]', 'adj.附加的；额外的', '1. He had to pay some additional charges. 他不得不付些附加费。 2. Additional material is overprinted in red. 附加材料是用红色加印上的。 3. You should know the additional responsibilities that are incidental to the job. 你该知道做这项工作要承担额外责任。 4. We are willing to pay an additional fee for immediate delivery . 我们愿意为即期交货支付一笔额外的费用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maglev', '[\'mæglev]', 'n.磁力悬浮火车 adj.磁力悬浮火车的', '1. You can take the maglev train at Pudong Airport. 你可以从浦东国际机场乘坐磁悬浮列车。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constrain', '[kən\'streɪn]', 'vt.强迫；限制', '1. I felt constrained to do what he told me. 做他叫我做的事,我心里很不舒服。 2. She tried to constrain herself from a cough in class. 上课时她竭力忍住不咳嗽。 3. Cold weather constrains the plant\'s growth. 寒冷的天气抑制了植物的生长。 4. Don\'t constrain yourself only to class study. 不要把自己的学习只局限于课堂。', '形容词: constrainable 副词: constrainedly 名词: constrainer 过去式: constrained 过去分词: constrained 现在分词: constraining 第三人称单数: constrains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brilliant', '[\'brɪljənt]', 'adj.卓越的；灿烂的；美妙的；杰出的；才华横溢的 n.宝石', '1. He has got brilliant achievements in the field of physics. 他在物理学方面已经取得了卓越的成就。 2. The brilliant sun lit up their rooms. 灿烂的阳光照亮了他们的屋子。 3. Memory is like a living book whose brilliant fragments worth reading a hundred times in my life. 回忆就像是一本生动的书,生活中那些精彩的片段令我百读不厌。 4. The novel is considered a brilliant performance. 这部小说被认为是出色的佳作。', '副词: brilliantly 名词: brilliantness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('synonym', '[\'sɪnənɪm]', 'n.近义词', '1. Don\'t mix up this pair of synonyms. 别把这两个近义词混淆了。 2. Zhuge Liang is a synonym for wisdom in folklore. 诸葛亮在民间传说中成了智慧的代名词。 3. A synonym is a word you use when you can\'t spell the word you first thought of. 同义词就是无法拼出首先想到的词后转而使用的词。', '形容词: synonymic 名词: synonymity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vibration', '[vaɪ\'breɪʃn]', 'n.震动；颤动', '1. Even at full speed the ship\'s engines cause very little vibration. 这条船即使全速前进，发动机的震动也很小。 2. The vibration during operation often caused the nuts to loosen. 机器运转时的震动常使螺母变得松动。 3. Your finger can feel the vibration on the violin string. 你的手指能感觉小提琴琴弦的颤动。 4. He told me that middle C is equivalent to 256 vibrations per second. 他告诉我说中央C音相当于每秒振动256次。', '形容词: vibrational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vote', '[voʊt]', 'n.选举权；投票；选举；投票结果 v.表决；选举；投票', '1. Give women the vote! 给妇女选举权！ 2. I suggested putting the matter to a vote, but the chairman demurred to it. 我建议对此事投票表决，但主席表示反对。 3. A large vote was polled. 投票踊跃。 4. He used his casting vote to block the motion. 他用他的投票反对动议的通过。 5. We are going to vote on the plan . 我们打算就这一提案进行表决。', '形容词: votable 名词: voter 过去式: voted 过去分词: voted 现在分词: voting 第三人称单数: votes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refute', '[rɪ\'fjuːt]', 'vt.驳斥；反驳；驳倒', '1. As for the Flat Earth theory, I believe I could refute it. 至于地平学说，我相信我能驳斥它。 2. Historical facts refute such a fallacy. 历史事实驳斥了这种谎言。 3. He had hardly finished when someone rose to refute his points. 他还没全说完，就有人起来反驳他的论点。 4. Nothing could refute her testimony that the driver was drunk. 她关于那个司机已经喝醉的证词无可辩驳。', '形容词: refutable 副词: refutably 名词: refutability 过去式: refuted 过去分词: refuted 现在分词: refuting 第三人称单数: refutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arouse', '[ə\'raʊz]', 'v.叫醒；唤醒；激起；睡醒', '1. It took her some time to arouse her husband. 她费了好一会儿才把丈夫叫醒。 2. Diana aroused them just before dawn. 戴安娜在黎明前唤醒了他们。 3. He fell into a sound sleep, don\'t arouse him. 他睡熟了，别唤醒他。 4. The slogan was designd to arouse the people. 该标语是为唤醒国民而拟定的。', '名词: arousal 过去式: aroused 过去分词: aroused 现在分词: arousing 第三人称单数: arouses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('submarine', '[ˌsʌbmə\'riːn]', 'n.潜水艇 adj.海面下的', '1. The frigate rammed the submarine. 护卫舰撞击了潜艇。 2. The ship was sunk by an atomic submarine. 这艘船是被一艘核潜艇击沉的。 3. A submarine glided silently through the water. 一艘潜水艇无声地在水中滑行。 4. At the first sign of danger the submarine will submerge. 一有危险迹象，潜艇就会潜入水中。 5. They are building a submarine cable tunnel. 他们正在建设一条海底电缆隧道。', '过去式: submarined 过去分词: submarined 现在分词: submarining 第三人称单数: submarines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maritime', '[\'mærɪtaɪm]', 'adj.海的；海上的；海事的', '1. England was a great maritime power. 英国曾是海上的强国。 2. This is a maritime form characterized by its low, branching habit and short, broad, densely bristly panicle. 这是一个以它的低，分枝体型和短，宽，密被刚毛的圆锥花序为特点的海上的形式。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mimic', '[\'mɪmɪk]', 'vt.模仿；模拟 n.模仿者；仿制品 adj.模仿的；假的', '1. He mimicked his uncle\'s voice and gestures perfectly. 他把叔叔的声音和姿态模仿得惟妙惟肖。 2. He could mimic all the teachers\' accents. 他能够模仿每位老师的口音。 3. You would like to mimic this plan on your test environment. 您需要在测试环境中模拟该计划。 4. One of my brothers is a wonderful mimic. 我的一个兄弟很善于模仿。 5. At the international level sport is frankly mimic warfare. 国际级比赛简直就是一场模拟战争。', '名词: mimicker 过去式: mimicked 过去分词: mimicked 现在分词: mimicking 第三人称单数: mimics');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prose', '[proʊz]', 'adj.散文的 n.散文', '1. This is a verbal translation of the prose. 这是那篇散文的逐字直译。 2. He has lately set forth a book on prose. 他最近出版一本论散文的著作。 3. His prose is written in elegant language. 他的散文写得十分优雅。 4. I want to glance over one time this piece of prose. 我想浏览一下这篇散文。', '过去式: prosed 过去分词: prosed 现在分词: prosing 第三人称单数: proses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('descend', '[dɪ\'send]', 'v.下降；降临 v.传下来；遗传 v.突然袭击；突然拜访', '1. The sun descended behind the hills. 太阳下山了。 2. I wish that the prices can descend. 但愿物价会下降。 3. I didn\'t expect him to descend to personal abuse. 我没料到他会堕落到对我进行人身攻击的地步。 4. At 6:30 p.m. the tropical darkness descends. 在傍晚六点半的时候,热带地区的黑夜降临。 5. The custom has descended to our day. 这一习俗一直传到今天。 6. Armed thieves descended on the helpless travelers. 一群武装盗贼袭击了无依无靠的旅客。', '形容词: descendible 过去式: descended 过去分词: descended 现在分词: descending 第三人称单数: descends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shear', '[ʃɪr]', 'n.修剪；剪下的东西；大剪刀 v.剪掉；剪；剥夺', '1. With a few quick snips of the shear, he pruned the bush. 他用大剪刀几下子就把灌木给修剪好了。 2. All her curls have been shorn off. 她的一头卷发被剪得精光。 3. I start shearing the sheep at the beginning of July. 我一般在7月初开始剪羊毛。', '名词: shearer 过去式: sheared 过去分词: sheared/shorn 现在分词: shearing 第三人称单数: shears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irreproachable', '[ˌɪrɪ\'proʊtʃəbl]', 'adj.无可指责的；无过失的', '1. Beyond any reasonable objection;irreproachable. 无懈可击的；无可指责的 2. Beyond any reasonable objection; irreproachable. 无懈可击的；无可指责的 3. His character is irreproachable. 他的品德是无可非难的。 4. His conduct is irreproachable (or beyond reproach). 他的行为无可非议。', '副词: irreproachably 名词: irreproachability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transient', '[\'trænʃnt]', 'adj.短暂的 n.短期居留者；<电>顺变电流', '1. Her feeling of depression was transient. 她那抑郁的心情一会儿就过去了。 2. Their happiness was transient,for the war broke out soon after they got married. 他们的幸福是短暂的，因为他们婚后不久就爆发了战争。 3. We stayed at the inn as transient guests. 我们在小酒馆中只作短暂停留。 4. We are just the transients at the hotel. 我们只是旅馆里的过往旅客。', '副词: transiently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shatter', '[\'ʃætər]', 'v.粉碎；毁坏；<口>使震骇；使精疲力尽 n.碎片', '1. The glass shattered. 这杯子碎了。 2. She shattered the cup when she dropped it on the floor. 她把杯子掉在地板上,摔得粉碎。 3. My dreams have been shattered. 我的梦想已经破灭了。 4. Her experience of divorce shattered her illusions about love. 她的离婚经历使她对爱情的幻想破灭了。 5. The broken vase lay in shatters. 那只打碎了的花瓶的碎片撒了一地。', '副词: shatteringly 过去式: shattered 过去分词: shattered 现在分词: shattering 第三人称单数: shatters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('caterpillar', '[\'kætərpɪlər]', 'n.毛虫 Caterpillar. n.卡特彼勒(财富500强公司之一；总部所在地美国；主要经营工业农业设备)', '1. A caterpillar is the larva of a butterfly. 毛虫是蝴蝶的幼体。 2. The ugly caterpillar will change into a beautiful butterfly. 丑陋的毛虫会变成美丽的蝴蝶。 3. A caterpillar must pass through the cocoon stage to become a butterfly. 毛毛虫必须经过茧的阶段才能变成蝴蝶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intense', '[ɪn\'tens]', 'adj.强大的；紧张的；强烈的；激烈的；深刻的', '1. He\'s been under intense pressure. 他面对着很大的压力。 2. My work is so intense that I even have no time to take a rest. 我的工作非常紧张，以致于我没有时间休息。 3. Her feelings are so intense as to move the present into tears. 她的感情如此之切,使在场的人都流下了眼泪。 4. There was intense competition between the rival companies to get the contract. 为得到这份合同,各不相让的两家公司展开了激烈的竞争。', '副词: intensely 比较级: intenser 最高级: intensest 名词: intenseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grasp', '[ɡræsp]', 'n.把握；领会；抓紧 vt.领会；抓住；紧握', '1. She has a good grasp of the English language. 她精通英语。 2. She has a comprehensive grasp of the subject. 她已全面掌握了这一学科。 3. I kept her hands in my grasp. 我紧握着她的手。 4. I grasped the main point of the speech. 我领会了这篇演讲的要点。', '过去式: grasped 过去分词: grasped 现在分词: grasping 第三人称单数: grasps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('underestimate', '[ˌʌndər\'estɪmeɪt]', 'n.低估 v.低估', '1. The figure of $10 million was a serious underestimate. 一千万美元这个数据是一个严重的低估。 2. It seems to have been due to his consistent underestimate of her political weight. 看来是由于希思一贯低估她的政治能量。 3. Never underestimate the power of a woman. 决不要低估妇女的力量。 4. Don\'t underestimate the difficulties of the work. 不要低估了这项工作的艰巨性。', '名词: underestimation 过去式: underestimated 过去分词: underestimated 现在分词: underestimating 第三人称单数: underestimates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('peninsula', '[pə\'nɪnsələ]', 'n.半岛', '1. His house is located on the tip of the peninsula. 他的房子位于半岛的顶端。 2. Leizhou Peninsula lies opposite Hainan Island. 雷州半岛正对着海南岛。', '形容词: peninsular');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('modest', '[\'mɑːdɪst]', 'adj.谦虚的；适度的；端庄的；有节制的', '1. We should be modest and prudent. 我们应该谦虚谨慎。 2. She is very modest about her success. 她对自己的成就很谦虚。 3. I bought the house at a modest price. 我以适中的价格买下了这所房子。 4. Young girls must be modest in speech, dress and behavior. 年轻姑娘必须言词谨慎，衣着得体，行为端庄。', '副词: modestly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nucleus', '[\'nuːkliəs]', 'n.核；核心；细胞核；原子核', '1. A nucleus can have only one Y-chromosome. 一个核可以仅有一个Y染色体。 2. These council will form the nucleus of a future regime. 这些委员会将成为一个未来政权的核心。 3. These paintings will form the nucleus of a new collection. 这些油画将是新收藏品的核心。 4. These 1000 books will form the nucleus of the new school library. 这一千本书将构成学校新图书馆藏书的基础。', '名词复数: nuclei');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abstruse', '[əb\'struːs]', 'adj.深奥的', '1. Philosophical semantics is too abstruse to understand. 哲学语义学深奥难懂。 2. Einstein\'s theory of relativity is very abstruse. 爱因斯坦的相对论非常难懂。', '副词: abstrusely 名词: abstruseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affinity', '[ə\'fɪnəti]', 'n.姻亲；密切关系；吸引力', '1. He is not an impartial witness because of his affinity with the accused. 他不是公正的见证人,因为他与被告有姻亲关系。 2. There is an affinity between Chinese and Japanese character. 汉字与日文之间有密切关系。 3. She feels a strong affinity to him. 她感到他对她有很强的吸引力。 4. This substance has an affinity for water. 这物质和水有亲和力。', '名词复数: affinities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accompany', '[ə\'kʌmpəni]', 'vt.陪伴；伴随...发生；补充；给 ... 伴奏 vi.伴奏', '1. She asked me to accompany her to the airport. 她要求我陪她到机场去。 2. Lightning usually accompanies thunder. 闪电通常伴有雷声。 3. The text is accompanied by illustration. 正文附有插图。 4. The singer was accompanied on the piano by her sister. 女歌手由她姐姐钢琴伴奏。 5. In the singer\'s eyes,she accompanied magnificently. 在那名歌手的眼里,她伴奏得精彩极了。', '过去式: accompanied 过去分词: accompanied 现在分词: accompanying 第三人称单数: accompanies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disarming', '[dɪs\'ɑːrmɪŋ]', 'adj.消除敌意的；解除疑虑的 动词disarm的现在分词形式.', '1. He flashed her a disarming smile. 他朝她笑了一下，让她消消气。 2. They outlined their aims with disarming frankness. 他们友好坦诚地简述了他们的宗旨。 3. He inquired into his visitors\' problems with disarming frankness. 他以使人无法反驳的坦率态度探询他的来宾们的问题。 4. We didn\'t trust him at first, but his charming manner completely disarmed us. 我们开始时并不信任他，但他令人愉快的举止完全消除了我们的疑虑。', '副词: disarmingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coexist', '[ˌkoʊɪɡ\'zɪst]', 'v.同时存在(于同一处)；共存；共处', '1. He will fight them relentlessly and refuse to coexist with them under the same sky. 他不断地攻击它们，不肯与它们共同生存在一个天空下面。 2. I know the human being and fish can coexist peacefully. 我知道人类和鱼可以和平并存。 3. Our foreign policy is to coexist with other countries. 我们的外交政策是和其它国家和平共处。', '形容词: coexistent 名词: coexistence 过去式: coexisted 过去分词: coexisted 现在分词: coexisting 第三人称单数: coexists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obstinate', '[\'ɑːbstɪnət]', 'adj.固执的；倔强的；不易屈服的；（病）难治的', '1. The obstinate child refused to answer. 这固执的孩子拒绝回答。 2. Because their hearts had turned hard, stubborn and obstinate. 重点是在于他们的心已经是硬的，是固执的，是顽固的。 3. He examined my obstinate expression, and switched to another line of attack. 他打量着一脸倔强的我，又转移战地。 4. Only a man full of the milk of human kindness could have continued to befriend the proud and obstinate young man. 只有天性善良的人才会和这个性情高傲脾气倔强的年轻人继续交往。', '副词: obstinately 名词: obstinateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aggregate', '[\'æɡrɪɡət]', 'adj.合计的；总的 n.总计；进球总数；集料 v.（使）聚集；总计', '1. What were your aggregate wages last year? 去年你的工资一共是多少? 2. The cause of unemployment was inadequate aggregate demand. 失业的原因在于总需求不足。 3. Manager wants to know the aggregate sales in that market. 经理想知道那个市场的总销售量。 4. The tax increases will, in the aggregate, cause much hardship. 增加税收归结起来将造成很多困难。 5. Occasionally the cells might aggregate to form lentoid bodies. 偶而，细胞能聚集形成类晶体球体。', '形容词: aggregative 副词: aggregately 名词: aggregation 过去式: aggregated 过去分词: aggregated 现在分词: aggregating 第三人称单数: aggregates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('humane', '[hjuː\'meɪn]', 'adj.仁慈的；人道的', '1. A humane society always does well by its old people. 一个仁慈的社会对待老人总是很好。 2. Accommodate the interests of infected patients in a sensitie and humane manner. 以一个灵敏和仁慈的方式调和感染病人的利益。 3. The logical answer, in this case, is the humane one. 既然如此，那么合乎逻辑的答案就是人道的那种选择。 4. The purpose of this public festival was to promote a healthy and humane lifestyle. 这个公开的庆祝活动目的是要倡导健康及合乎人道的生活方式。', '副词: humanely 名词: humaneness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('audit', '[\'ɔːdɪt]', 'n.审计；查帐 vt.旁听；审计', '1. As usual, the yearly audit will take place in December. 跟往常一样，年度审计将在十二月份进行。 2. They work non-stop to finish the audit on time. 他们不停地工作以按期完成审计工作。 3. He had read the audit chief\'s report about the embezzlement and cash loss. 他已读过查帐部主任关于这件贪污加现款盗窃案的报告。 4. But everyone was there, helping to examine the bank\'s records for the special audit Mr. Bell was taking. 但是每个人都在那儿，帮助检查银行的记录，因为贝尔先生正在进行特别查帐。 5. Which course do you want to audit? 你想旁听哪门课?', '过去式: audited 过去分词: audited 现在分词: auditing 第三人称单数: audits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ironic', '[aɪ\'rɑːnɪk]', 'adj.说反话的；讽刺的', '1. At the early stage of Requirements Definition, brainstorming assumes a somewhat ironic purpose. 在需求定义阶段的早期进行头脑风暴在某种程度上呈现出一种说反话的意图。 2. In his early and lightly ironic work, his criticism was restrained. 在他早期稍含讽刺的作品里，批评口吻也很克制。 3. It would be ironic if, in the process, it is creating its own eventual crisis. 然而，如果这过程中，中国最终是在制造自己的危机，那将是十分讽刺的。', '副词: ironically 异体字: ironical 名词: ironicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('violation', '[ˌvaɪə\'leɪʃn]', 'n.违反；违背；妨碍', '1. The drunken driver was brought to the police station for violation of traffic regulations. 这个喝醉了的司机因违反交通规则而被带进了警察局。 2. From now on any violation of the regulation must be cruelly punished. 今后任何违反秩序的行为会受到严厉惩罚。 3. They were in open violation of the treaty. 他们公然违反条约。 4. Stealing was a violation of my ethics. 偷盗违背了我的道德标准。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('donor', '[\'doʊnər]', 'n.捐赠人；施主；供者', '1. The donor\'s identity is a close secret. 捐赠人的身分是一个严加保守的秘密。 2. The donor prefers to remain anonymous. 捐赠者希望不披露姓名。 3. His body rejected the liver of the donor. 他的身体排斥捐赠者的肝。 4. It was also counting on getting food aid from South Korea, its biggest donor. 朝鲜当局当时还指望从其最大施主韩国获得粮食援助。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('collateral', '[kə\'lætərəl]', 'adj.旁系的；并行的；附属的 n.附属担保物；支亲；副保', '1. Cousins are collateral relatives. 表堂兄弟姊妹都是旁系亲属。 2. Security market and property right trade market are two collateral markets. 证券市场和产权交易市场是两个并行的市场。 3. He offered me a lot of collateral readings. 他为我提供了许多平行读物。 4. He offered some collateral evidences. 他提供了一些旁证。 5. He used his house as a collateral for the loan. 他用房子作这笔贷款的担保品。', '副词: collaterally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tip', '[tɪp]', 'n.小费；小建议；轻拍；尖端，顶端；倾斜，翻倒 v.给小费；装顶端；倾斜；翻倒', '1. He charged me 20 yuan for tip. 他向我要了20元小费. 2. It\'s common to leave a tip in many Western countries. 在很多西方国家,给小费是很平常的。 3. This manual is full of useful tips. 这本小册子里有很多实用的小建议。 4. Did you remember to tip the porter? 你记得给搬运工小费了吗？', '名词: tipper 过去式: tipped 过去分词: tipped 现在分词: tipping 第三人称单数: tips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('turkey', '[\'tɜːrki]', 'n.火鸡；笨蛋；失败之作 n.[T-]土耳其', '1. It\'s traditional in England to eat turkey on Christmas Day. 圣诞节时吃火鸡是英格兰的传统。 2. People often drink white wine with turkey. 人们经常边吃火鸡肉边喝白葡萄酒。 3. Russia thereupon declared war upon Turkey. 俄国于是对土耳其宣战。', '名词复数: turkeys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shove', '[ʃʌv]', 'v.推挤；撞；乱塞；乱放 n.推；挤', '1. Don\'t try to shove all the work onto me! 别把工作都推给我！ 2. He dragged her out of the door and shoved her into the street. 他把她拖到门口，猛地把她推到马路上。 3. Then suddenly, Old Grizzly gave Brown Bear a big shove. 突然间，老灰熊给棕色熊一个重重的推撞。 4. Bunt was probably a nickname given to him at school, for going around with his head lowered, ready to bump and shove anybody aside. 铁头可能是他上学时得的绰号，那时他总低着头走路，一副准备随时一头把人撞到一边的架势。 5. The car won\'t start. Can you give it a shove? 这车子启动不了。你能不能推它一把?', '名词: shover 过去式: shoved 过去分词: shoved 现在分词: shoving 第三人称单数: shoves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suitcase', '[\'suːtkeɪs]', 'n.手提箱', '1. My wife compacted my clothes in a suitcase. 妻子把我的衣服紧塞在手提箱里。 2. We\'ve got a spare suitcase but it\'s not very get-at-able. 我们有个多余的手提箱，但是不太容易拿出来。 3. He stuffed the suitcase with his clothes. 他把衣服塞满手提箱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exhibit', '[ɪɡ\'zɪbɪt]', 'v.展览；陈列；展示；表现 n.展品；展览', '1. Many unearthed cultural relics were exhibited at the museum. 博物馆展出了许多出土文物。 2. He was given a whole room to exhibit his paintings. 整个房间用来展览他的画作。 3. She exhibited great powers of endurance during the climb. 她在攀登过程中表现出极大的耐力。 4. They deprecated the new exhibit. 他们很不赞成新展品。', '形容词: exhibitory 名词: exhibitor 过去式: exhibited 过去分词: exhibited 现在分词: exhibiting 第三人称单数: exhibits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grim', '[ɡrɪm]', 'adj.严厉的；冷酷的；可怕的；不愉快的', '1. Her face wore a grim, set look. 她脸上显出严厉、 木然的神情。 2. His expression was grim when he told them they had lost their job. 当他告诉他们说他们已被解雇时，他的表情十分冷酷。 3. A grim and unsightly picture met his eye. 一幅可怕和难看的情景映入他的眼帘。 4. I had a pretty grim day yesterday. 我昨天很不愉快。', '副词: grimly 比较级: grimmer 最高级: grimmest 名词: grimness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fable', '[\'feɪbl]', 'n.寓言；神话；无稽之谈 v.讲寓言；虚构', '1. Fables often have animals as the main characters. 寓言常以动物为主角。 2. The following passage was quoted from a well-known fable. 接下来这一段是出自一篇有名的寓言。 3. We may take the story of Job for a history or a fable. 我们可以把关于约伯的故事当作历史或者当作神话。 4. We have to learn to distinguish fact from fable. 我们应当学会识别真伪。 5. He fabled about his lot. 他编造自己的身世。', '名词: fabler 过去式: fabled 过去分词: fabled 现在分词: fabling 第三人称单数: fables');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consciously', '[\'kɒnʃəsli]', 'adv.有意识地；自觉地', '1. He is consciously trying to overcome his weakness. 他有意识地在克服自己的缺点。 2. She realized how tense she was and consciously relaxed. 她发觉自己很紧张，于是有意识地放松了一下。 3. If I want to repair my credit rating, then I must be consciously aware of my spending habits all the time. 如果我想修理我的信用评级，那么我一定要自觉地意识到自己的开销习惯，在所有时间。 4. In order to maintain order, consciously soldiers surrounded a circle hand in hand, the stars around the inside. 为了维持秩序，士兵们自觉地手拉手围成一个圈，把明星们围在里面。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('split', '[splɪt]', 'v.分裂；将…分成若干部分；分摊；分离；劈开；裂开；<俚>离开 n.劈开；裂口；分裂；一份；水果冰淇淋 adj.分裂的；意见分歧的', '1. The party split into petty factions. 该党分裂成若干小派系。 2. The vote split the Labour Party. 那场选举使工党分裂了。 3. She split the class into groups of four. 她按四人一组把全班分成若干小组。 4. The arrow just split the apple in half. 箭把苹果分成两半。 5. Frost caused the split in the rock. 霜冻使岩石裂了一条缝。 6. They believe the killer has a split personality. 他们认为这个凶手人格分裂。', '名词: splitter 过去式: split 过去分词: split 现在分词: splitting 第三人称单数: splits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('verdict', '[\'vɜːrdɪkt]', 'n.裁决；定论', '1. The jury announced their verdict. 陪审团做出了裁决。 2. The jury brought in a verdict of guilty. 陪审团作出有罪的裁决。 3. \"A science fiction cannot not be regarded as a mere entertainment, but in fact it tells the reader much more.\" \"科幻小说不能简单地看成是供消遣的，而实际上它给读者展示更深刻的内容。\" 4. They have had the verdict of the electors. 他们已经知道了选举人的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eloquent', '[\'eləkwənt]', 'adj.雄辩的；有口才的；动人的', '1. He addressed the audience in an eloquent speech. 他向听众发表了雄辩的演说。 2. Eloquent elephants telephoned other eloquent elephants. 雄辩的大象打电话给其他雄辩的大象。 3. Such an eloquent man will easily talk us down. 这样一个有口才的人很容易把我们驳得无话说。 4. An eloquent speaker is one skilled in the use of words. 有口才的人善于用词。', '副词: eloquently 名词: eloquentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remains', '[rɪ\'meɪnz]', 'n.剩余物；遗迹；遗体', '1. After maintenance the main remains and remainders are left on the domain. 维修之后，主要遗骸和剩余物留在了领地上。 2. After the wheat crop has been gathered, many farmers burn the remains and plough the ash into the soil, so as to enrich it. 小麦收割完成后，农夫们把剩余物烧掉，然后用犁把灰埋入地里，使土地更肥沃。 3. Not a vestige of the abbey remains. 那修道院的遗迹已荡然无存。 4. They have found prehistoric remains. 他们发现了史前遗迹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elucidate', '[i\'luːsɪdeɪt]', 'v.阐明；说明', '1. There is no need for him to elucidate. 他没有必要去详细阐明。 2. I will try to elucidate what I think the problems are. 我将尽力阐明我认为问题的所在。 3. Please elucidate the reasons for your action. 请说明你采取行动的理由。 4. This is the aspect that China does not explain or elucidate in public forums. 在公开场合，中国并没有对后面的观点作出解释说明。', '形容词: elucidative 名词: elucidation 过去式: elucidated 过去分词: elucidated 现在分词: elucidating 第三人称单数: elucidates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emigrate', '[\'emɪɡreɪt]', 'v.移居；移民', '1. I\'ll emigrate to the western woods. 我要移居到西部的丛林里去。 2. He\'s decided to emigrate and start a new life in America. 他决定移居美国，开始新的生活。 3. Many people had to emigrate during the Nazi period. 在纳粹党期间许多人不得不移民。 4. I don\'t like your plan to emigrate to Canada. 我不赞成你移民加拿大的计划。', '名词: emigration 过去式: emigrated 过去分词: emigrated 现在分词: emigrating 第三人称单数: emigrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('renovate', '[\'renəveɪt]', 'vt.修理；翻新；革新；刷新', '1. They are going to renovate the old furniture. 他们准备将旧家具整修一番。 2. I\'ve decided to renovate the garden next year. 我准备明年把这座庭园修葺一下。 3. We purchase your technology chiefly in order to renovate our old equipment. 我们购买你们的技术，主要是为了改造我们的旧设备。 4. It cost much to renovate old college buildings at the University of Chang Jiang. 翻新长江大学的旧校舍花费很大。', '名词: renovation 过去式: renovated 过去分词: renovated 现在分词: renovating 第三人称单数: renovates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spine', '[spaɪn]', 'n.脊柱；脊椎；书脊；尖刺', '1. His spine developed a slight curve. 他的脊柱有点弯曲。 2. He got an injury to his spine when he fell off his horse. 他从马上摔下来，伤了脊梁骨。 3. Crimp spine on pages for permanent binding. 用装订机装订好书脊。 4. A little red cover with a broken spine. 那书有一个红红的封面和破败的书脊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gasp', '[ɡæsp]', 'v.喘气；喘息；渴望 n.喘气', '1. He gasped out the message. 他喘着气说出了这个消息。 2. I gasped as I jumped into the cold river. 当我跳进冰冷的河里时，简直透不过气来。 3. I gasped with surprise at the unexpected news. 听到意外的消息，我惊讶地吸了一口气。 4. The exhausted runner was gasping for air. 那人跑得疲惫已极，上气不接下气。 5. Michelle recognized him and gave a gasp of shock. 米歇尔认出了他，吃惊地直喘气。', '过去式: gasped 过去分词: gasped 现在分词: gasping 第三人称单数: gasps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bison', '[\'baɪsn]', 'n.野牛', '1. American bison are very large. 美洲野牛非常巨大。 2. Herds of bison live in the park. 公园内住有成群的野牛。 3. The killing of the bison changed the whole wildlife of the plains. 杀害野牛引起整个平原的野生动植物的改变。 4. Large herds of bison used to live on the plains of North America. 大群的野牛过去曾生活在北美大草原上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('admission', '[əd\'mɪʃn]', 'n.承认；入会费；许可', '1. He is a coward by his own admission. 他自己承认是个胆小鬼。 2. He was, on his own admission, impulsive by nature. 他承认自己生性易于感情冲动。 3. Do they charge for admission? 入场要收费吗? 4. The charge for admission is US$5. 入场费五美元。', '形容词: admissive');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('derange', '[dɪ\'reɪndʒ]', 'vt.扰乱；使发狂', '1. So few men were present to derange the harmony of the wilderness. 极少有人去扰乱林子里的平静。', '名词: derangement 过去式: deranged 过去分词: deranged 现在分词: deranging 第三人称单数: deranges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ignoble', '[ɪɡ\'noʊbl]', 'adj.平民的；卑贱的；卑鄙的；不光彩的', '1. Some very great men have come from ignoble families. 有些伟人出身低微。 2. He is an ignoble man. 他是一个卑鄙的小人。 3. He has achieved whatever work it was in him to do, the fear of death is somewhat abject and ignoble. 完成了他份内要做的所有工作，怕死就有点儿卑鄙和不光彩了。', '副词: ignobly 名词: ignobility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('succumb', '[sə\'kʌm]', 'v.屈从；死', '1. The mangabeys have been able to resist SIV, while the macaques, much like humans, inevitably succumb to it. 白眉猴已经能够抵抗猴免疫缺陷病毒，而恒河猴，就像人类一样，不可避免地屈从于它。 2. Some advocates of leaving say the presence of Western infidels in Afghanistan is so provocative that it makes Pakistan itself likelier to succumb to the jihadists. 一些赞成撤军的人士声称西方异教者在阿富汗的存在势力太具有挑衅意味而使巴基斯坦自己更有可能屈从与圣战分子。 3. Malnourished children are more likely to succumb to infections. 营养不良的儿童更有可能死于感染。 4. The aged denizen of the forest is doomed to succumb to the woodman\'s stroke! 多年在林中享有权利的香柏树，竟死在樵夫手下！', '过去式: succumbed 过去分词: succumbed 现在分词: succumbing 第三人称单数: succumbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exempt', '[ɪɡ\'zempt]', 'adj.免除的 vt.免除 n.免税者；被免除义务者', '1. He is exempt from military service. 他免服兵役。 2. These houses are exempt from paying rates. 这些房子是免付捐税的。 3. Poor eyesight will exempt you from military service. 视力不佳将使你免服兵役。 4. We hope you will exempt us from taxes. 希望贵方能给予我们免征关税待遇。', '形容词: exemptible 过去式: exempted 过去分词: exempted 现在分词: exempting 第三人称单数: exempts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('declaration', '[ˌdeklə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.宣言；宣布；申报', '1. The declaration was published in August 1687. 这份宣言是1687年8月公布的。 2. She read the declaration aloud for everyone to hear it clearly. 为了使大家都能听得清楚,她将宣言高声读了一遍。 3. These events led to the declaration of war. 这些事件导致了宣战。 4. Please show your customs declaration form. 请出示你的海关申报单。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disgust', '[dɪs\'ɡʌst]', 'n.厌恶；憎恶；反感 vt.使厌恶；使作呕', '1. She turned away in disgust. 她厌恶地转过脸去。 2. His behavior filled her with disgust. 她对他的行为充满了厌恶。 3. He returned downstairs in disgust. 他厌恶地转身下楼。 4. I can only feel disgust for these criminals. 对这些罪犯我只感到憎恶。 5. His ideas disgust me; they are terrible. 他的一些想法使我很反感，它们实在是太可怕了。', '过去式: disgusted 过去分词: disgusted 现在分词: disgusting 第三人称单数: disgusts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bog', '[bɑːɡ]', 'n. 沼泽 v. 使 ... 陷于泥沼； 陷于困境', '1. Ren took Gerin to the bog moon of Bogden. 伦把婕琳带到博格登的沼泽卫星。 2. In later years when the bog is drained, the peat can be dug out and used as fuel. 再过几年，当沼泽干涸之后，泥煤可以挖出来用作燃料。', '形容词: boggy 名词: bogginess 过去式: bogged 过去分词: bogged 现在分词: bogging 第三人称单数: bogs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heading', '[\'hedɪŋ]', 'n.标题；题目；航向 动词head的现在分词.', '1. See sections Section and Heading for more info. 更多信息请见章节和标题。 2. The heading was in large letters. 标题是用大号字母印刷的。 3. Choose a descriptive subject heading. 选择适当题目。 4. Imagine, too, that you are heading for the Arctic. 想像你正要航向北极，而且需要带五枚照明弹到达目的地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('horizon', '[hə\'raɪzn]', 'n.地平线；眼界；范围', '1. The lights were blinking on the horizon. 灯光在地平线上闪烁着。 2. The sun rose above the horizon. 太阳升到地平线上。 3. Forget the horizon then you can fly high. 要想飞得高,就要把地平线忘掉。 4. Travel broadens one\'s horizons. 旅行可开阔人的眼界。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intelligible', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.可理解的；明白易懂的；清楚的', '1. His theory is not intelligible to us. 他的理论我们无法理解。 2. The book is intelligible to anyone. 这本书任何人都看得懂。 3. The answers must be intelligible, but they do not have to be in complete sentences. 答案必须要清楚明晰，不过不必是完整的句子。', '副词: intelligibly 名词: intelligibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('statue', '[\'stætʃuː]', 'n.雕像；塑像', '1. The statue is twice life-size. 该雕像大小为实体的两倍。 2. They decided to perpetuate the memory of their leader by erecting a statue. 他们为永远纪念那位领袖决定建一座雕像。 3. The statue was carved out of marble. 这座雕像是用大理石雕刻的。 4. The statue of Jefferson was big as life. 杰斐逊的塑像和真人一样大小。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agile', '[\'ædʒl]', 'adj.（动作）敏捷的；灵活的；（头脑）机灵的', '1. He was quick and agile and he didn\'t mind losing. 他敏捷，灵活，输了不在乎。 2. You might sometimes need an agile negotiator. 你有时会需要一个灵活的谈判代表。 3. The problem that he answers newsman is very agile. 他回答新闻记者的问题很灵活。 4. One need an agile mind to solve puzzles. 解谜必须有机灵的头脑。', '副词: agilely 名词: agileness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lag', '[læɡ]', 'v.落后；减退；缓慢进行 n.落后；时间间隔', '1. Some of the runners in the race began to lag. 参加比赛的运动员中有一些开始落後了。 2. The children always lag behind when we go for a walk. 我们出去散步时，孩子们总是落在后面。 3. Interest lags in such matters. 对这类事情的兴趣慢慢减少了。 4. It takes a lot of time to catch up with a cultural lag. 文化的落后需要长时间才能赶上。', '名词: lagger 过去式: lagged 过去分词: lagged 现在分词: lagging 第三人称单数: lags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('copper', '[\'kɑːpər]', 'n.铜；铜币；警察；紫铜色；有紫铜色翅膀的小蝴蝶 vt.镀铜', '1. Copper conducts electricity better than iron does. 铜的导电性比铁强。 2. The shop sells copper vessels of all shapes. 这家商店出售各种形状的铜器皿。 3. He polished up the old copper coins. 他把旧铜币擦亮。 4. I gave him a few coppers. 我给了他几个铜币。 5. Zinc base die castings are always copper plated in cyanide baths. 锌基合金的压铸件总是在氰化镀液中镀铜。', '形容词: coppery 过去式: coppered 过去分词: coppered 现在分词: coppering 第三人称单数: coppers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remainder', '[rɪ\'meɪndər]', 'n.剩余物；其余的人；[数]余数 vt.廉价出售', '1. The remainder must be paid by the end of June. 剩余部分的金额必须在月底前付清。 2. He spent the remainder of his life in the country. 他在乡村度过余生。 3. Nine people came in and the remainder stayed outside. 9个人进来，余下的人留在外面。 4. Take 4 from 9 and the remainder is 5. 9除以4余数为5。', '过去式: remaindered 过去分词: remaindered 现在分词: remaindering 第三人称单数: remainders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dazzling', '[ˈdæzlɪŋ]', 'adj.令人眼花缭乱的；耀眼的 动词dazzle的现在分词.', '1. It lends vibrancy, dazzling color, and deep savoriness to foods. 它带来有活力感，令人眼花缭乱的颜色，和浓郁口味的食物。 2. He pointed out to her the dazzling fittings of the coach. 他向她指点着车厢里那许多令人眼花缭乱的装饰。 3. A dazzling streak lit up the sky. 一道耀眼的闪电照亮了天空。 4. But those dazzling statistics mask an often more mundane reality. 但这些耀眼的统计数字掩饰了一个通常不那么出色的现实。', '副词: dazzlingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lay', '[leɪ]', 'lie的过去式. v.放置；躺下；打赌；设计；击倒；产卵；使平静；压平 n.地形；位置；叙事短诗；交媾 adj.外行的；世俗的', '1. You may lay it on the table. 你可以把它放在桌子上。 2. I lay down not so much to sleep as to think. 我躺下来与其说是要睡觉，倒不如说是要思考。 3. I\'ll lay odds of three to one that he gets the job. 我以三比一的赔率打赌，他能得到那份工作。 4. He showed us how to lay out a printed page. 他告诉我们怎样设计版面。 5. He knows the lay of the land here. 他了解这里的地形。 6. A lay opinion as to the seriousness of the disease. 关于这种疾病的非专业的意见', '过去式: laid 过去分词: laid 现在分词: laying 第三人称单数: lays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('phonetics', '[fə\'netɪks]', 'n.语音学', '1. She\'s an authority on phonetics. 她是语音学权威。 2. Phonetics is the science of sounds. 语音学是一门语音的科学。 3. Daniel Jones is generally referred to be the foremost authority on phonetics. 丹尼尔·琼斯通常被认为是语音学方面的最高权威。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rustic', '[\'rʌstɪk]', 'adj.乡村的；纯朴的；手工粗糙的；土气的 n.乡下人；村夫；农民', '1. His rage was soon calmed down by the rustic peace. 乡村的宁静很快就使他的怒气平静下来。 2. Visitors from cosmopolitan cities were held spellbound by the rustic scenery. 来自大都会的游客被乡村景色迷住了。 3. The village has a certain rustic charm. 这个村子有某一种质朴的魅力。 4. But little Pearl was not clad in rustic weeds. 当然，小珠儿穿的并不是破衣烂衫。 5. The fellow is as handsome a rustic as need be seen. 这个家伙作为一个乡下人是够漂亮的。', '副词: rustically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('significantly', '[sɪɡ\'nɪfɪkəntli]', 'adv.意味深长地；意义深远地；重要地；较大地', '1. She paused significantly before she answered. 她在回答之前意味深长地停顿了一下。 2. Significantly New York is left out of this list. 意味深长的是纽约这个城市的名字从名单中划掉了。 3. Significantly, he did not deny that there might be an election. 颇具意义的是,他没否认可能要进行选举。 4. The police released him but, significantly, they didn\'t give him back his passport. 警方释放了他，但是没有把护照还给他，这是有特殊用意的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('float', '[floʊt]', 'v.漂浮；浮现；飘动；提出 n.浮标；漂浮物；漂浮', '1. There is not enough water to float the ship. 没有足够的水使船漂浮起来。 2. These plants float on the surface of the water. 这些植物漂浮在水面上。 3. They float the canoe out into the middle of the river. 他们将独木舟漂浮到河中央。 4. Survival bobbing lets you float for a long time on your stomach. 救生浮游就是让你长时间地仰卧着漂浮在水上。 5. Pay attention to your float! 注意你的浮标！', '形容词: floatable 过去式: floated 过去分词: floated 现在分词: floating 第三人称单数: floats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evaporate', '[ɪ\'væpəreɪt]', 'v.蒸发；失去水分；消失', '1. If you heat the water,it will evaporate. 你要是把水加热，水会蒸发的。 2. He was afraid his savings would evaporate overnight. 他担心他的储蓄隔夜就蒸发了。 3. Once you have seen fear and depression evaporate in the hot, intense beacon of awareness, you want to repeat the process. 但你发现在热烈的，强度的觉知下，恐惧与压抑消失了，你会想去重复这个过程。 4. Nechyba and Vigdor also show that the peer effects evaporate once they consider the quality of teaching. 内希巴和维格多还表示，一旦他们将教育质量因素纳入考虑范围，同伴效应就消失了。', '形容词: evaporative 副词: evaporatively 名词: evaporation 过去式: evaporated 过去分词: evaporated 现在分词: evaporating 第三人称单数: evaporates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('guideline', '[\'ɡaɪdlaɪn]', 'n.指导方针；准则', '1. This guideline stresses the deterrence of war. 这一方针注重遏制战争的爆发。 2. The only guideline is to reach the best possible result. 唯一的指导方针,就是获得最好的可能的结果。 3. They see the law only as a general guideline. 他们视法律为一般的准则 4. This guideline is established by general consent. 这个纲领是经多数人同意而制定的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sum', '[sʌm]', 'n.金额；总数；要点 v.概括；总结；归纳；总计', '1. I had to spend a large sum of money to get it back. 我得花一大笔钱才把它弄回来。 2. I save a nice little sum out of my wages each week. 我从每周的工资中节省一笔可观的金额。 3. The sum of 5 and 3 is 8. 五加三的总和是八。 4. Is that the sum of what you\'ve done in the last two years? 这就是你最近两年中完成的全部数量吗？ 5. We can sum up the main point of the lesson in three sentences. 我们可以用三句话来概括本课要点。', '过去式: summed 过去分词: summed 现在分词: summing 第三人称单数: sums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laser', '[\'leɪzər]', 'n.激光；镭射', '1. Lasers can be used to perform operations nowadays. 现在激光可以用来做手术。 2. He monopolizes the laser printer. 他独占了这台激光打印机。 3. The doctor finished the operation, but his success depended on the backroom boys who had invented the new laser scalpel. 医生做完了手术，但他的成功有赖于那些发明了新型激光手术刀的研究人员。 4. A laser reflection will occur at each laminate substrate. 每一片玻璃都会产生一个镭射反射。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exemplary', '[ɪɡ\'zempləri]', 'adj.可仿效的；模范的', '1. Saintly individuals who lead exemplary lives imbue their environments with the holiness that accrues from their spiritual practices. 圣洁的个体通过他们从精神实践中产生的神圣来引导可仿效的生命浸透他们的环境。 2. And this exemplary treatment of herself by herself constitutes her presence. 这种作为模范的自我待遇，正构成了她的风度。', '副词: exemplarily 名词: exemplariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refine', '[rɪ\'faɪn]', 'v.精炼；改进；使更文雅', '1. The oil will be refined. 这些石油将被精炼。 2. Their daily work is to refine crude oil. 他们每天的工作是精炼原油。 3. Sugar, oil and metals are refined before use. 糖, 油和金属在使用前须先提炼。 4. We shall have to refine on our methods of advertising. 我们得进一步改进做广告的方法。', '名词: refiner 过去式: refined 过去分词: refined 现在分词: refining 第三人称单数: refines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imperative', '[ɪm\'perətɪv]', 'adj.紧要的；必要的；祈使的 n.紧要的事；命令；义务；驱使', '1. It is imperative that we make a quick decision. 我们要尽快做出决定。 2. It\'s imperative that you apologize to him immediately. 你必须立即向他道歉。 3. \"Go!\" is in the imperative mood. “Go！”是祈使语气的句子。 4. Survival is our first imperative. 我们当务之急是设法生存下来。', '副词: imperatively 名词: imperativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mock', '[mɑːk]', 'v.嘲弄；嘲笑；模仿 n.嘲笑；模仿；戏弄 adj.假的；伪装的；模拟的', '1. He went to church only to mock. 他到教堂去只是为了嘲弄宗教。 2. We should not mock at other people\'s religious beliefs. 我们不应该嘲笑别人的宗教信仰。 3. I have a pet monkey which attempts to mock all my actions. 我养了一只猴子当宠物，它试图模仿我所有的动作。 4. His bully make a mock of all the fine thing he say about kindness to others. 他那恃强欺弱的行为对于他所说的待人友善的漂亮言词是一个嘲弄。 5. She handed him the envelope with mock solemnity. 她装出一副郑重其事的样子，把信封交给他。', '副词: mockingly 名词: mocker 过去式: mocked 过去分词: mocked 现在分词: mocking 第三人称单数: mocks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squabble', '[\'skwɑːbl]', 'v.（为琐事）争论；口角 n.争论；口角', '1. No man will squabble over a nickel. 没有人会为了五分钱而吵架。 2. I hate to squabble with my wife about [over] money. 我厌恶为钱的事与太太争吵。 3. The silly family\'s squabble became a joke in the neighborhood. 这场无聊的家庭纠纷已经成为街坊邻居的笑柄。 4. A judge may have to sort out the immediate squabble. 法官可能不得不解决当前的争吵。', '名词: squabbler 过去式: squabbled 过去分词: squabbled 现在分词: squabbling 第三人称单数: squabbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spontaneity', '[ˌspɑːntə\'neɪəti]', 'n.自然性', '1. The romantic spontaneity and courage are gone. 浪漫的自然感和勇气均荡然无存。 2. But the very essence of creativity is spontaneity. 但是创造力的精髓在于自发性。', '名词复数: spontaneities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('highlight', '[\'haɪlaɪt]', 'vt.强调；照亮；加亮；使 ... 显得重要；使突出 n.加亮区；精彩部分；最重要的细节或事件；闪光点 [计算机] 醒目', '1. Both books highlight the human element of science. 两本书都重点谈到科学中人的因素。 2. Mr Bush also wants to highlight African successes. 布什先生想突出强调一下非洲的成就。 3. What would you highlight about them? 对于他们你想强调些什么呢? 4. Of course we must highlight that the system can hardly be inaccurate. 当然我们必须强调这一点，即该系统根本不可能出错。 5. It is one of the highlights of the match. 这是比赛中最精彩的项目之一。', '过去式: highlighted 过去分词: highlighted 现在分词: highlighting 第三人称单数: highlights');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sloth', '[sloʊθ]', 'n.树獭；懒惰', '1. Sloths live in trees and move very slowly. 树獭生活在树上而且行动缓慢。 2. He has kept sloth out. 他已经克服了懒惰。 3. Sloth is one of human being\'s weaknesses. 人性的弱点之一是懒惰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dependent', '[dɪ\'pendənt]', 'adj.依靠的；依赖的；从属的', '1. All is dependent on your decision. 一切看你的决心而定。 2. The child is dependent on his parents for support. 这个小孩靠他的父母养活。 3. She is still financially dependent on her parents. 她在经济上仍然依靠父母。 4. The country\'s economy is dependent on tourism. 该国经济依赖於旅游业。', '副词: dependently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('esteem', '[ɪ\'stiːm]', 'n.尊敬 vt.尊敬；认为', '1. We all have great esteem for you. 我们都非常敬重您。 2. All his students held him in high esteem. 他的学生对他都很尊敬。 3. No one can esteem you more than I do. 没有人会比我更敬重你。 4. He is esteemed for his courage. 他因有勇气而受人尊敬。', '过去式: esteemed 过去分词: esteemed 现在分词: esteeming 第三人称单数: esteems');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ample', '[\'æmpl]', 'adj.丰富的；宽敞的；充足的', '1. He has got ample stage experience, and won\'t get stage fright. 他有丰富的舞台经验，不会怵场的。 2. The region developed by leaps and bounds because of its ample mineral resources. 这个地区由于有丰富的矿藏,所以发展得很快。 3. The house has an ample parlor. 这座房子有宽敞的客厅。 4. Our sitting room is ample and bright. 我们的居室宽敞明亮。', '副词: amply 比较级: ampler 最高级: amplest 名词: ampleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invaluable', '[ɪn\'væljuəbl]', 'adj.无价的；非常珍贵的', '1. But the experience they will gain is invaluable. 但他们从此获得的经验是无价的。 2. His experience proved an invaluable help. 他的经验被证明是无价之宝。 3. The painting is an invaluable treasure. 这幅画是无价之宝。 4. This set of ancient china is invaluable. 这套古瓷器非常珍贵。', '副词: invaluably 名词: invaluableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('symbol', '[\'sɪmbl]', 'n.符号；象征；标志', '1. The chemical symbol for copper is \"Cu\". 铜的化学符号是Cu。 2. The dove is the symbol of peace. 鸽子是和平的象征。 3. The river-sea dividing marker must be a symbol which separates the Yalu River from the Yellow Sea. 江海分界碑,这里就是鸭绿江和黄海分界的标志吧。', '过去式: symboled 过去分词: symboled 现在分词: symboling 第三人称单数: symbols');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flag', '[flæɡ]', 'n.旗；旗帜；信号旗 vt.(以旗子)标出 v.无力地下垂；减退；枯萎', '1. Flags are fluttering in the breeze. 旗子在风中飘扬。 2. The flag was flown at half-staff. 那旗帜降了半旗。 3. The flag was aflutter in the air. 旗帜在空中飘扬。 4. The signal flag is fully in our sight from this position. 我从这个位置完全可以看到信号旗。 5. Halfway through the race he began to flag. 赛跑到一半他开始有点跑不动了。', '名词: flagger 过去式: flagged 过去分词: flagged 现在分词: flagging 第三人称单数: flags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comment', '[\'kɑːment]', 'n.注释；评论；闲话 v.评论；注释', '1. The comment is recorded in the event log. 此注释将记录在事件日志中。 2. He made no comments on our proposal. 他对我们的建议没有作评论。 3. Her strange behavior caused a good deal of comment. 她的反常行为引起了不少闲话。 4. He commented that it was an excellent film. 他评论这电影很精彩。', '过去式: commented 过去分词: commented 现在分词: commenting 第三人称单数: comments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outrage', '[\'aʊtreɪdʒ]', 'n.暴行；愤怒；义愤 vt.凌辱；激怒', '1. The Government has been dilatory in condemning the outrage. 政府迟迟才谴责是次暴行。 2. We should never forget the outrage committed by the Japanese invaders. 我们永远都不应该忘记日本侵略者犯下的暴行。 3. All right-minded people will be surely shocked by this outrage. 凡是有正义感的人都一定会对这种暴行感到震惊。 4. Her answer was greeted with cries of outrage. 她的回答引起了一片愤怒的吼叫。 5. He was outraged by their behavior. 他们的行为使他感到愤慨。', '过去式: outraged 过去分词: outraged 现在分词: outraging 第三人称单数: outrages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('profile', '[\'proʊfaɪl]', 'n.侧面；轮廓；形象；简介 v.描绘 ... 轮廓；评论人物', '1. I photographed him in profile. 我从侧面给他拍照。 2. She is prettier in profile than at full face. 她的侧面比正面好看。 3. We could see the profile of a distant hill if it is very clear. 如果天气晴朗, 我们可看到远山的轮廓。 4. The deal will certainly raise the company\'s international profile. 这宗交易肯定会提高这家公司的国际形象。 5. The huge trees were profiled against the night sky. 在夜空的映衬下显出大树的轮廓。', '名词: profiler 过去式: profiled 过去分词: profiled 现在分词: profiling 第三人称单数: profiles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preach', '[priːtʃ]', 'vt.讲道；说教 vi.传道；训诫', '1. The priest preached a sermon on the need of charity. 牧师在布道会上宣讲慈爱的必要。 2. Those people go around preaching revolution. 那些人到处宣扬革命。 3. Christ preached that we should love each other. 基督在布道中说人们应该互敬互爱。 4. She preached economy as the best means of solving the crisis. 她大力鼓吹节约是解决危机的关键。 5. The priest preached to the congregation about the Sermon on the Mount. 那位祭司就山中圣训向会众说教。', '副词: preachingly 过去式: preached 过去分词: preached 现在分词: preaching 第三人称单数: preaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stylistic', '[staɪ\'lɪstɪk]', 'adj.风格上的；文体上；格式上的；体裁上的', '1. All their works have stylistic similarities. 他们的作品风格相近。 2. The city architecture shows stylistic variation. 城市建筑学展现出格调上的多样性。 3. At present they are studying the stylistic device. 现在他们正在研究文体表现手法。 4. Lianzhu is the combination of stylistic vivacity and seriousness. 摘要连珠体是游戏体裁与严肃主题的结合体。', '副词: stylistically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unconscious', '[ʌn\'kɑːnʃəs]', 'adj.失去知觉的；无意的', '1. He lay unconscious in a pool of blood. 他失去知觉，躺在血泊之中。 2. This wounded soldier was unconscious from his loss of blood. 这名伤员由于失血过多而昏迷不醒。 3. He is unconscious of having made a serious error. 他未察觉到已犯了严重的错误。 4. I was unconscious of her presence. 我不知道她在场。', '副词: unconsciously 名词: unconsciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constantly', '[\'kɑːnstəntli]', 'adv.不断地；经常地', '1. Language is constantly and gradually evolving. 语言在不断地缓慢发展。 2. She was constantly spurred on by a fear of failure. 对失败的恐惧不断地激励着她。 3. The area was constantly hit by drought. 这地区经常遭到旱灾。 4. He constantly writes articles for the local paper. 他经常给当地报纸写文章。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('engulf', '[ɪn\'ɡʌlf]', 'vt.吞没；席卷；吞噬', '1. The waves engulfed the boat. 大浪吞没了小舟。 2. The stormy sea engulfed the small motor sailboat. 汹涌的大海吞没了那艘小机帆船。 3. The country was engulfed in civil war. 该国陷入内战。 4. A wave of grief engulfed them. 一阵悲伤吞噬了他们。', '名词: engulfment 过去式: engulfed 过去分词: engulfed 现在分词: engulfing 第三人称单数: engulfs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('category', '[\'kætəɡɔːri]', 'n.种类；类别；范畴', '1. There are different categories of books in a library. 图书馆里有各种不同种类的书籍。 2. They fall into different categories. 他们属于不同的类别。 3. They misplaced this book under another category. 他们把它错放到另一个类别去了。 4. How can a scientific category have its derivatives? 科学范畴何以能衍生?', '名词复数: categories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dissolve', '[dɪ\'zɑːlv]', 'vt.使溶解；解散；消除；解决(问题)；使沮丧 vi.溶解；液化；消散；变得模糊 n.叠化画面', '1. Dissolve one tablet in warm water. 将一片药片溶解在热水中。 2. The parliament was dissolved. 议会解散了。 3. As president, he can dissolve parliament on a whim. 作为总统，他可以随意解散议会。 4. Plasmin is the main protease to break down and dissolve thrombus. 胞浆素是消除和分解血栓的主要蛋白酶。 5. Ice dissolved in the warm weather. 冰在温暖的天气中溶化了。', '形容词: dissolvable 名词: dissolver 过去式: dissolved 过去分词: dissolved 现在分词: dissolving 第三人称单数: dissolves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ridiculous', '[rɪ\'dɪkjələs]', 'adj.荒谬的；可笑的', '1. His social pretensions make him appear ridiculous. 他冒充上流社会人士而出尽洋相。 2. His aristocratic manners seemed ridiculous in this poor area. 在这个贫穷的地区，他的贵族气派显得很可笑。 3. I\'ll show you how to settle such ridiculous stuff. 你瞧我怎样来对付这种无稽之谈。 4. That\'s ridiculous. 那太荒唐了。', '副词: ridiculously 名词: ridiculousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('savings', '[\'seɪvɪŋz]', 'n.储蓄', '1. The old man kept his savings in the bank. 老人把他的储蓄存在银行里。 2. Paying for that new carpet has eaten into my savings. 付新地毯的款用去了我的一部分储蓄。 3. She withdrew all her savings and left the country. 她把全部存款取出后离开了那个国家。 4. He has squandered all his savings on drink. 他把存的钱全买酒喝了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('costume', '[\'kɑːstuːm]', 'n.服装；剧装 vt.提供服装；为 ... 设计服装 adj.服装打扮的', '1. This traditional costume is of indigo blue. 这件传统服装是靛蓝色的。 2. Her funny costume caused much mirthful laughter among the guests. 她那滑稽的服装引得客人哄堂大笑。 3. The kimono is part of the national costume of Japan. 和服是日本民族服装的一部分。 4. We patched up a costume for the play . 我们临时凑成了一件戏装。 5. Jane costumed a historical play. 简曾为一出历史剧设计服装。 6. A friend of mine was asked to a costume ball a short time ago. 不久前，我的一个朋友被邀请参加一个化装舞会。', '过去式: costumed 过去分词: costumed 现在分词: costuming 第三人称单数: costumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incredible', '[ɪn\'kredəbl]', 'adj.难以置信的；惊人的', '1. I think it\'s incredible. 我认为这是难以置信的。 2. That\'s the most incredible coincidence I\'ve ever heard of! 那是我听说过的最难以置信的巧合！ 3. He showed an incredible indifference to the matter. 他对这件事表现出令人难以置信的淡漠。 4. He has an incredible house! 他有一所极美的房子！', '副词: incredibly 名词: incredibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('moisten', '[\'mɔɪsn]', 'v.弄湿；使湿润；变湿', '1. She moistened a tissue and gently wiped the dust off the necklace. 她沾湿了一块纸巾，轻轻擦去项链上的灰尘。 2. He used a dampener to moisten the shirts before he ironed them. 在熨衬衣前，他用加湿器先湿润了一下。 3. Her eyes moistened as she listened to the sad story. 听着这悲伤的故事，她的眼睛湿润了。', '名词: moistener 过去式: moistened 过去分词: moistened 现在分词: moistening 第三人称单数: moistens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('countless', '[\'kaʊntləs]', 'adj.无数的；多的数不清的', '1. There are countless stars in the sky. 天上有无数的星星。 2. In early spring sunlight scattered countless dust. 初春的阳光散落无数的尘埃。 3. There were countless trees in the forest. 森林中有数不清的树。 4. We received cash, hams, turkeys, and countless boxes of candy. 我们收到了现金、火腿、火鸡，还有数不清的盒糖。', '副词: countlessly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('league', '[liːɡ]', 'n.种类；社团；联盟；同盟；里格（长度单位，约为3英里或3海里） v.（使）结盟', '1. They are not in the same league. 他们的水平有高低。 2. Our club is a member of the Football League. 我们的俱乐部是足球联合会的一员。 3. Most of us in our class are League members. 我们班上大多数是团员。 4. He is a member of the Ivy League. 他是长春藤联合会的一员。 5. We must league together against this threat. 面对这种威胁我们必须联合起来。', '过去式: leagued 过去分词: leagued 现在分词: leaguing 第三人称单数: leagues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('superb', '[suː\'pɜːrb]', 'adj.极好的', '1. The sports facilities are superb in this city. 这个城市的运动设施是一流的。 2. The goalkeeper brought off a superb save. 守门员漂亮地救出了险球。 3. Ideas will come to you easily and some will prove to be superb. 你总很容易就能想到好计划，其中一些将得到极好的证实。', '副词: superbly 名词: superbness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infection', '[ɪn\'fekʃn]', 'n.传染；传染病；影响', '1. Are you sure there is no danger of infection now? 你敢不敢肯定现在已经没有传染的危险了? 2. This infection is transmitted by mosquitoes. 这种传染病是由蚊子传染的。 3. He was infected with a latent infection. 他被感染了一种潜伏性的传染病。 4. This new type of infection is resistant to antibiotics. 这种新的传染病对抗菌素有抗药性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('synopsis', '[sɪ\'nɑːpsɪs]', 'n.摘要；概要', '1. He just wants the synopsis and the list of options. 他只想要选项的摘要和列表。 2. The synopsis of the book is very good. 这本书的梗概非常好。 3. Biographies, filmographies and synopsis can also be sent on a separate sheet. 您也可以将个人简介、电影作品目录及参赛作品介绍作为附件寄来。', '名词复数: synopses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('greedy', '[\'ɡriːdi]', 'adj.贪婪的', '1. He is a greedy capitalist. 他是一个贪婪的资本家。 2. He looked at the shop window with greedy eyes. 他用贪婪的眼光看着商店的橱窗。', '副词: greedily 比较级: greedier 最高级: greediest 名词: greediness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barrel', '[\'bærəl]', 'n.桶；枪管；一桶的量；炮管；大量；笔管；汽油桶 vi.快速移动 vt.把 ... 装桶', '1. Beer swilled around the bottom of the barrel. 啤酒在桶底晃荡。 2. The beer comes out of the barrel under pressure. 啤酒受到压力从桶中流出。 3. This barrel contains 50 litres. 这个桶容量为50升。 4. He made a barrel with staves by himself. 他自己用桶板做了一只桶。 5. They planned to barrel the beer next Monday. 他们打算下星期一把啤酒装桶。', '过去式: barreled/barrelled 过去分词: barreled/barrelled 现在分词: barreling/barrelling 第三人称单数: barrels/barrels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('retain', '[rɪ\'teɪn]', 'vt.保持；保留；记住；聘请', '1. His speech could not retain the interest of his audience. 他的讲话不能保持住听众的兴趣。 2. I will retain my right. 我将保留我的权力。 3. Does it retain the key elements of the original story? 它是否保留了原作的关键要素? 4. She has a good memory and finds it easy to retain matters. 她记忆力好,很容易记住事情。', '形容词: retainable 名词: retainability 过去式: retained 过去分词: retained 现在分词: retaining 第三人称单数: retains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unanimity', '[ˌjuːnə\'nɪməti]', 'n.一致同意；全体一致', '1. Our discussions led to complete unanimity. 我们的讨论取得了完全一致的意见。 2. Nothing marred the unanimity of the proceedings. 议事未受任何阻碍获得一致通过。 3. They finally agreed to that plan in unanimity. 他们最后一致地通过了那个计划。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('edge', '[edʒ]', 'n.边缘；优势；边；刀口 vt.给 ... 加上边；缓慢横过；使锋利 vi.徐徐前进', '1. Look out! You could fall off the edge here! 小心!你会从这边缘掉下的。 2. New houses have mushroomed on the edge of the town. 城市边缘的新建房屋犹如雨后春笋。 3. In the second half of the game, the home team got the edge on the visitors and kept it. 比赛下半场,主队比客队略占上风,并把这一优势保持到终场。 4. Because of the high exchange rate, our products have lost their competitive edge. 由于汇率很高, 我们的产品失去了竞争优势。 5. She lost a handkerchief edged with blue. 她丢了一块镶蓝边的手绢。 6. Unemployment will edge up, but not by much. 失业率将缓慢上升，但增幅不是很大。', '形容词: edgeless 过去式: edged 过去分词: edged 现在分词: edging 第三人称单数: edges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detrimental', '[ˌdetrɪ\'mentl]', 'adj.有害的 n.有害的人或事', '1. Lack of sleep is detrimental to one\'s health. 缺乏睡眠有害健康。 2. Smoking is detrimental to health. 吸烟封健康是有害的。 3. He works long hours to the detriment of his health. 他长时间的工作，有损健康。', '副词: detrimentally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incriminate', '[ɪn\'krɪmɪneɪt]', 'v.牵连；控告；使负罪', '1. She refused to make a statement to the police in case she incriminated herself. 她拒绝向警方作陈述以免受连累。 2. No one can be forced to incriminate himself. 没有人有义务证明自己有罪。 3. He is accused of perjury with the intention of incriminate his employer. 他被控告犯有意图加罪于其雇主的伪证罪。', '形容词: incriminatory 名词: incrimination 过去式: incriminated 过去分词: incriminated 现在分词: incriminating 第三人称单数: incriminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('temperament', '[\'temprəmənt]', 'n.气质；性情', '1. He really has a leader temperament. 他真的有些领袖气质。 2. He is a man with an artistic temperament. 他是个有艺术家气质的男子。 3. I\'ve got a mild temperament. 我的性情很温和。 4. The two brothers have entirely different temperaments. 他们兄弟俩的性情完全不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('matchless', '[\'mætʃləs]', 'adj.无敌的；无比的', '1. I saw in the street a woman of matchless beauty. 我在路上看见一个绝代佳人。 2. Mr Mei Lanfang\'s singing skill is matchless in the world. 梅兰芳先生的唱功无与伦比。 3. Her matchless beauty is beyond description. 她那旷世无双的美貌无法形容。 4. All of them make a matchless beautiful picture. 所有这些构成了一幅无比美丽的画卷。', '副词: matchlessly 名词: matchlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ingenious', '[ɪn\'dʒiːniəs]', 'adj.机灵的；精巧的；有独创性的', '1. The ingenious boy made a radio set for himself. 这个聪明的男孩自己做了一台收音机。 2. He invented an ingenious excuse for being late. 他为迟到编造了一个巧妙的借口。 3. It was an intricate and ingenious system. 这是一个复杂而精致的体系。 4. I never heard anything more ingenious than your suggestion. 我从来没有听见过象你这样有独创性的提法。', '副词: ingeniously 名词: ingeniousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tenement', '[\'tenəmənt]', 'n.房屋；住户；租户', '1. He lives in a tenement block. 他住在一家廉价公寓楼里。 2. They lived in a crumbling Glasgow tenement. 他们住在格拉斯哥一栋摇摇欲坠的廉价公寓里。 3. The great photographer posed them in front of a row of tenement. 摄影大师让他们在一排公寓房面前摆好姿势。 4. In the tenement yard, there wasn\'t a single tree or flower. 在这个大杂院里，连一棵树一棵花都没有。', '形容词: tenemental');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agency', '[\'eɪdʒənsi]', 'n.代理；代理处；政府机构', '1. I hope we can see eye to eye about the other terms of the agency then. 我希望到那时候我们能在代理协议的其他条款上能取得一致意见。 2. I got this job through an employment agency. 我通过职业介绍所找到了这份工作。 3. They resigned their child to an adoption agency. 他们把自己的孩子交给了一家收养机构。 4. The agent is the person who works for a government agency in secret. 特工人员是为政府部门秘密工作的人。', '名词复数: agencies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transpire', '[træn\'spaɪər]', 'v.蒸发；排出；泄露', '1. This, it later transpired, was untrue. 此事后来得知不属实。 2. It transpired that the gang had had a contact inside the bank. 据报这伙匪徒在银行里有内应。 3. You\'re meeting him tomorrow? Let me know what transpires. 你是明天见他吗? 把见面後的情况告诉我。', '过去式: transpired 过去分词: transpired 现在分词: transpiring 第三人称单数: transpires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mediocre', '[ˌmiːdi\'oʊkər]', 'adj.平庸的；平凡的', '1. This leads to mediocre training, fitness, and performance. 这将导致平庸的训练，体能和成绩。 2. Calico Rackham Jack had mediocre accomplishments as a pirate. 卡利科拉克姆杰克平庸的成绩已成为海盗。 3. That foursome alone should make Arizona very competitive in the mediocre National League West. 这个四人组合将会让亚利桑纳在平凡的国家联盟西区非常具有竞争力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wag', '[wæɡ]', 'v.(狗)摇摆(尾巴)；(狗尾巴)摇摆；摇(头或手表示不赞成)；逃学；饶舌；<古>离别 n.摇摆；诙谐幽默的人；逃学', '1. Dogs wag their tails when they are pleased. 狗一高兴就摇尾巴。 2. The dog\'s tail wagged. 那只狗的尾巴摇摆着。 3. They often persuaded me to wag school. 他们常劝我逃学。 4. The news set tongues wagging. 那则消息使人们议论纷纷。 5. The dog greeted its master with a wag of its tail. 狗摇着尾巴迎接主人。', '名词: wagger 过去式: wagged 过去分词: wagged 现在分词: wagging 第三人称单数: wags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('armor', '[\'ɑːmə]', 'n.盔甲；装甲', '1. In the past, knights used to wear armor in battle. 在过去，骑士在战斗中身穿盔甲。 2. Never underestimate the power of extra armor. 永远不要低估额外的盔甲。 3. My armor will crush your pathetic forces. 我的装甲部队将会打垮你可怜的军队。 4. Dreams are the armor for our fragile hearts. 梦想是装甲为我们易碎的心脏。', '过去式: armored 过去分词: armored 现在分词: armoring 第三人称单数: armors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tenacious', '[tə\'neɪʃəs]', 'adj.抓紧的；坚决的；(记忆力)强的', '1. He hold on to my arm with a tenacious grip. 他紧紧抓住我的手臂不放。 2. The eagle seized its prey in a tenacious grip. 鹰将捕获物紧紧抓住。 3. She is tenacious in defence of her rights. 她坚决维护自己的权利. 4. He is tenacious of his opinions. 他固执己见。', '副词: tenaciously 名词: tenaciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acknowledge', '[ək\'nɑːlɪdʒ]', 'vt.承认；告知收到；公认；表示感谢；注意到', '1. We acknowledged the need for reform. 我们承认改革的需要。 2. Please acknowledge this cheque as soon as you receive it. 收到该支票后,请立即告知。 3. We hope you can acknowledge your mistake in public. 希望你当众认错。 4. We are sending you some money in acknowledgement of your valuable help. 我们送些酬劳，对您的大力协助聊表谢意。', '形容词: acknowledgeable 过去式: acknowledged 过去分词: acknowledged 现在分词: acknowledging 第三人称单数: acknowledges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('various', '[\'veriəs]', 'adj.各种各样的', '1. There are various ways of solving the problem. 有各种各样解决问题的方法。 2. He decided to leave school for various reasons . 由于各种各样的原因,他决定离开学校。 3. Their hobbies are many and various. 他们的业余爱好五花八门。', '副词: variously 名词: variousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conference', '[\'kɒnfərəns]', 'n.会议；讨论会；协商会；会谈', '1. He is in conference. 他正在开会。 2. An international conference will be held in Beijing next month. 一个国际性的会议下月将在北京举行。 3. There will be a banquet following the conference. 会议过后将有一个宴会。 4. We are all fully confident that the conference will be a great success. 我们都有充分的信心,这次会议将会非常成功。', '形容词: conferential');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hospitable', '[hɑː\'spɪtəbl]', 'adj.好客的；殷勤的；易于接受的；宜人的', '1. It does not take much to be a hospitable host. 做一个好客的主人不需要很高的条件。 2. Americans have the reputation of being very hospitable people. 美国人有非常好客的美誉。', '副词: hospitably');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dejected', '[dɪ\'dʒektɪd]', 'adj.沮丧的；灰心的 动词deject的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Repeated failure had left them feeling very dejected. 他们三番五次失败后情绪非常低落。 2. He was dejected to learn that he had failed the examination. 得知考试不及格,他便垂头丧气。', '副词: dejectedly 名词: dejectedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('regardless', '[rɪ\'ɡɑːrdləs]', 'adj.不顾的；不注意的 adv.不顾', '1. He is regardless of the result. 他不顾虑结果。 2. He crushed the bloom with regardless tread. 他毫不在意一脚践踏了鲜花。 3. I protested, but she carried on regardless. 我极力反对，但她置之不理仍一意孤行。 4. They decorated the house regardless of cost. 他们不惜工本装修这栋房子。', '副词: regardlessly 名词: regardlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preponderance', '[prɪ\'pɑːndərəns]', 'n.优势；多数', '1. I had some preponderance than him also. 我还有比他优越的地方。 2. There is not sufficient preponderance over enemy in the front line. 在前线，我们对于敌人并没有显著的优势。 3. There is a preponderance of tiger in the forest. 森林里老虎数量最多。', '异体字: preponderancy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revert', '[rɪ\'vɜːrt]', 'vi.恢复；回复；归还', '1. You should try not to revert to your old eating habits. 你应该尽力不要恢复到你过去的饮食习惯。 2. He reverted to smoking when under stress. 他因受到压力又恢复了吸烟的习惯。 3. We\'ll revert to your enquiry as soon as fresh supplies are available. 一旦有货，我们就回复你方询价。 4. If he dies without leaving an heir, his lands will revert to the state. 如果他死后无继承人，其土地将复归国家所有。', '形容词: revertible 名词: reverter 过去式: reverted 过去分词: reverted 现在分词: reverting 第三人称单数: reverts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('debate', '[dɪ\'beɪt]', 'n.辩论；讨论 vt.争论；思考 vi.辩论', '1. After a long debate, the house of commons approved the bill. 经过长时间的辩论，下议院通过了议案。 2. We had a long debate as to whether we should spend so much money on space technology. 至于我们要否花那么多钱在太空技术上,我们辩论了很久。 3. Her resignation caused much public debate. 她辞职一事引起群众议论纷纷。 4. There has been heated debate about whether the film should be allowed. 关于这场电影是否该通过,人们展开了热烈的讨论。 5. I don\'t wish to debate my opinions with you. 我不想就我的看法同你辩论。 6. This is a question that they have often debated. 这是个他们常讨论的问题。', '名词: debatement 过去式: debated 过去分词: debated 现在分词: debating 第三人称单数: debates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sardonic', '[sɑːr\'dɑːnɪk]', 'adj.讥讽的；嘲笑的；冷笑的', '1. There was a sardonic expression on her face. 她脸上有一种嘲讽的表情。 2. There is little of Satie\'s sardonic wit to be heard in Skempton\'s works. 在斯开普顿的作品里几乎听不到萨蒂那种讥讽的智慧。 3. Her voice faded away at the sardonic gleam in his eyes. 在他嘲笑的眼神中，她的声音慢慢低下去。 4. Creole started into something else, it was almost sardonic. 克里奥尔又开始了，这次几乎是在嘲笑。', '副词: sardonically 名词: sardonicism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('digest', '[\'dɑɪdʒɛst]', 'n.摘要 vt.消化；理解 vi.消化', '1. This is a digest of the week\'s news. 这是一周新闻摘要。 2. The baby is too small to digest meat. 婴儿太小,吃肉不消化。 3. Saliva helps one chew and digest food. 唾液能帮助咀嚼和消化食物。 4. It took me some time to digest what I had heard. 我花了一些时间才把听到的东西弄明白。 5. This rich food doesn\'t digest easily. 这种油腻的食物不易消化。', '过去式: digested 过去分词: digested 现在分词: digesting 第三人称单数: digests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('primal', '[\'praɪml]', 'adj.最初的；原始的；主要的', '1. Then primal sedateness came back. 而后世界又恢复了最初的安详。 2. I\'m sure that I will actualize the primal promise. 我确信我能实现最初的诺言。 3. In these primal skies, there was no Moon. 在原始的天空里，没有月亮。 4. Money was a primal necessity to them. 钱是他们最主要的需要。', '名词: primality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clue', '[kluː]', 'n.线索；提示', '1. There is no clue to the identity of the thief. 没有确定窃贼身分的线索。 2. We have no clue as to where she went after she left home. 我们对她离家後去往何处毫无线索。 3. They are now trying to chase down all possible clues. 他们现在正在设法寻找一切可能的线索。 4. I gave him another clue, but he still didn\'t twig (the answer). 我又提示他一次，他还是不理解(那答案).', '过去式: clued 过去分词: clued 现在分词: clueing/cluing 第三人称单数: clues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remote', '[rɪ\'moʊt]', 'adj.遥远的；偏僻的；远程的；(感情等)距离很大 n.远程操作', '1. The most remote two points in this world are two estranged hearts. 人世间相距最远的两点,是两颗隔膜的心。 2. This is a village remote from the madding crowd. 这是一个远离喧嚣尘世的村庄。 3. Mail comes to this remote village only once a week. 邮车每周只到这个偏僻的村庄一次。 4. The bomb was exploded by remote control. 这颗炸弹是遥控引爆的。 5. Actuation is often desired for process automation, precision timing, and remote operation not possible with manual valves alone. 执行机构经常用于实现紧靠手动阀门无法实现的工艺过程的自动化，准确定时，以及远程操作。', '副词: remotely 比较级: remoter 最高级: remotest 名词: remoteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heedless', '[\'hiːdləs]', 'adj.不注意的；不留心的', '1. He is heedless of the noises out of the windows. 他没有注意到窗外的嘈杂声。 2. We were heedless of danger in the condition. 我们在那种条件下忽视了危险。 3. He is heedless of anything around him. 他对周围的事物毫不留心。', '副词: heedlessly 名词: heedlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('longitude', '[\'lɑːndʒətuːd]', 'n.经度', '1. Leonids don\'t peak over your longitude. 狮子座流星雨极大期不会在你的那个经度出现。 2. Prolong the sponge along the longitude and latitude at an altitude. 沿着经度和纬度在一高度延长海绵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unseemly', '[ʌn\'siːmli]', 'adj.不体面的；不相配的；不适宜的 adv.不适当地', '1. Everyone was shocked by his unseemly conduct. 大家都被他不得体的举动震惊了。 2. His social position allows him of no unseemly behaviour in public. 他的社会地位不容许他在公共场合有行为不妥之处。', '比较级: unseemlier 最高级: unseemliest 名词: unseemliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impassioned', '[ɪm\'pæʃnd]', 'adj.慷慨激昂的；热烈的 动词impassion的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. He made an impassioned speech in our school. 他在我们学校做了一次慷慨激昂的演讲。 2. He kept this impassioned doings a secret almost from himself 他把他这种感情热烈的行动保守得极秘密，几乎连对自己都不泄露。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impotence', '[\'ɪmpətəns]', 'n.无能；[医]阳萎', '1. The power of love is its impotence. 爱的无限威力在于爱不堪一击。 2. His impotence to help made him despair. 他无力帮忙,感到很失望。 3. There is strength in numbers, but impotence in singlehandedness. 人多势众 4. The factory was also making fake male impotence drugs. 这家工厂还生产假冒的男用壮阳药品。', '异体字: impotency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nocturnal', '[nɑːk\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.在夜间的；（指生物）夜间活动的', '1. Stars are a nocturnal sight. 星星是夜间的景观。 2. Ali was his principal attendant during this nocturnal survey. 阿里陪着他作这次夜间视察。 3. A nocturnal animal hunts its food at night. 夜间活动的动物在夜间猎食。 4. The dormouse is a shy, nocturnal creature. 榛睡鼠是一种在夜间活动的胆小动物。', '副词: nocturnally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refreshing', '[rɪ\'freʃɪŋ]', 'adj.提神的；新鲜宜人的；与众不同的 动词refresh的现在分词形式.', '1. Love is the best refreshing potion. 爱情是生活最好的提神剂。 2. There is nothing as refreshing as lemon tea. 什麽都不如柠檬茶那样提神。 3. After a refreshing nap, Mr Adams was again his own man. 亚当斯先生睡了个好午觉，又恢复了精神。 4. The air is rather refreshing, I suppose. 我想，那里的空气应该很宜人。', '副词: refreshingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pervert', '[pər\'vɜːrt]', 'vt.误用；歪曲；曲解；败坏 n.变态；色狼', '1. Scientific knowledge was perverted to help cause destruction and war. 科学知识被滥用于破坏和战争。 2. To pervert what a person has said is to give a wrong meaning to it. 歪曲一个人所说的就是对其所说给予错误的理解。 3. He made an attempt to pervert the meaning of an innocent story. 他试图曲解了一个无辜故事的意义。 4. The corrupt man takes bribes to pervert the course of justice. 那个腐败的男人收受贿赂颠倒正义。 5. Cinema is the ultimate pervert art. 电影是终极的变态艺术。', '形容词: pervertible 名词: perverter 过去式: perverted 过去分词: perverted 现在分词: perverting 第三人称单数: perverts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tribal', '[\'traɪbl]', 'adj.部落的', '1. Vincent\'s father is a tribal chief. 文森特的父亲是一个部落的酋长。 2. They buried the man following the tribal customs. 他们按照部落习俗把那个人埋了。 3. The linguists went to study tribal languages in the field. 语言学家们去实地研究部落语言了。', '副词: tribally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('generate', '[\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'vt.产生；发生；引起', '1. 75% of France\'s electricity is generated by nuclear reactors. 法国75%25的电能产生于核反应堆。 2. We can\'t generate enough power for the entire city. 我们不能为整个城市产生足够的能量。 3. We need someone to generate new ideas. 我们需要有人出新主意。 4. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。', '过去式: generated 过去分词: generated 现在分词: generating 第三人称单数: generates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pertain', '[pər\'teɪn]', 'vi.关于；从属；适合', '1. This letter does not pertain to politics. 这封信的内容与政治无关。 2. Learning the specific set of vocabulary words that pertain to one\'s business becomes a simple task. 学习和自己行业有关的这组特殊字汇成为一件简单的工作。 3. They own the house and the land pertaining to it. 他们拥有这栋房子以及附属于它的土地。 4. It does not pertain to the young to instruct their elders. 年轻人不应该对老年人发号施令。', '过去式: pertained 过去分词: pertained 现在分词: pertaining 第三人称单数: pertains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bleak', '[bliːk]', 'adj.萧瑟的；阴郁的；严寒的；无希望的', '1. The bleak breeze blights the brightly blooming blossom. 萧瑟的微风吹枯了盛开着的花。 2. The bleak ground pullulated with jackrabbits. 荒凉的土地上到处是长耳大野兔。 3. The world was not always so bleak. 这个世界不是生来就如此凄冷的。 4. It\'s a bleak look-out for the coal industry as the number of pit closures increases. 煤井关闭的数目日多，煤炭工业前景暗淡。', '副词: bleakly 比较级: bleaker 最高级: bleakest 名词: bleakness 名词复数: bleak');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('regulate', '[\'reɡjuleɪt]', 'vt.调整；校准；管理；控制', '1. Specification could be regulated as buyer\'s request. 指标可根据客户要求进行调整。 2. Regretfully, we can\'t regulate the irregular liner on the gulf. 遗憾的是我们不能调整海湾上不定期的班船。 3. Your watch is always slow; it needs to be regulated. 你的手表总是慢，需要校准一下。 4. Accidents sometimes happen even in the best regulated families. 即便是在管理最好的家庭，事故有时也会发生的。', '形容词: regulative 过去式: regulated 过去分词: regulated 现在分词: regulating 第三人称单数: regulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imaginative', '[ɪ\'mædʒɪnətɪv]', 'adj.富于想象力的', '1. Scott was an imaginative writer. 司格特是位富于想象力的作家。 2. Money still talks, but in more imaginative ways. 金钱仍然是万能的，不过是通过更加富于想象力的方式。', '副词: imaginatively 名词: imaginativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stuffy', '[\'stʌfi]', 'adj.(房间等)不通气的；(人或事物)沉闷乏味的；自负的', '1. Lacking fresh air; stuffy. 不通风的缺乏新鲜空气的; 闷气的 2. The office was so stuffy that, knowing the Chief was away, the Secretary stripped to the shirt. 办公室里十分闷热，由于知道主任出去了，这个秘书脱得剩衬衫。 3. The atmosphere is very stuffy in here can we open a window? 这的空气很闷--咱们能把窗户打开吗? 4. Our office is really stuffy. 我们的办公室很闷。', '副词: stuffily 比较级: stuffier 最高级: stuffiest 名词: stuffiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('terrain', '[tə\'reɪn]', 'n.地带；地形', '1. The car blitzed through rough terrain. 这辆汽车长驱穿越了崎岖地带。 2. Valley glaciers are confined to valleys in mountainous terrain. 山谷冰川只限于多山地带的山谷。 3. It\'s a difficult terrain for tanks. 这是坦克作战的困难地形。 4. They stopped and began to reconnoitre the terrain. 他们停下来，开始勘测地形。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('article', '[\'ɑːrtɪkl]', 'n.文章；物品；条款；[语]冠词 vt.订契约', '1. She asked him to contribute a biweekly article on European affairs. 她让他每两周写一篇有关欧洲情况的文章。 2. If you don\'t return the article to the shop within a week, you forfeit your chance of getting your money back. 如果你不把物品归还商店，你就丧失了取回钱的机会。 3. Article 180 states that one third of the members must be women. 第180条规定,三分之一的成员必须为女性。 4. Today we\'ll discuss the use of the article. 今天我们讨论冠词的用法。 5. I am articled to a firm of lawyers. 我受雇在一家律师公司做见习生。', '过去式: articled 过去分词: articled 现在分词: articling 第三人称单数: articles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sympathetic', '[ˌsɪmpə\'θetɪk]', 'adj.同情的；共鸣的；赞同的 n.交感神经', '1. He took a sympathetic attitude toward my situation. 他对我的境遇抱同情的态度. 2. We are sympathetic with the flood sufferers. 我们同情水灾受难者。 3. She was sympathetic to my ideas. 她对我的想法表示支持。 4. They were quite sympathetic to our proposals. 他们非常赞同我们的建议。', '副词: sympathetically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plumb', '[plʌm]', 'v.（用铅垂）测量；探测 n.铅锤；垂直 adj.垂直的；<口>完全的 adv.恰恰；<口>彻底地', '1. We need to plumb the line. 我们需要用铅垂测量这条线。 2. We begin to plumb the mysteries of the universe. 我们开始探索宇宙的奥秘。 3. It was unprofitable to plumb that sort of thing. 这种事弄个水落石出没有什么好处。 4. Bricklayers and carpenters often use plumb lines . 瓦工和木工经常使用铅垂线。 5. Is this wall plumb? 这墙是垂直的吗？ 6. The bullet hit him plumb between the eyes. 子弹正好打在他的双眼之间。', '形容词: plumbable 过去式: plumbed 过去分词: plumbed 现在分词: plumbing 第三人称单数: plumbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pilot', '[\'paɪlət]', 'n.飞行员；领航员；试播节目；<美>排障器；[机]导向器 v.驾驶；领航；向导；试点 adj.试验性的；引导的', '1. A pilot must be awake to the changes in the weather. 飞行员必须警觉天气的变化。 2. Mark used to be a pilot on the Mississippi River. 马克曾在密西西比河上当过领航员。 3. JULES I think her biggest deal was she starred in a pilot. 朱尔斯：我想她最重要的演出是在一个试片里担任主角。 4. When did you learn to pilot an airplane? 你什么时候学会驾驶飞机的? 5. We are doing a pilot study to see if the new product will sell well. 我们正在为这种新产品做试销调查，看它的销路好不好。', '过去式: piloted 过去分词: piloted 现在分词: piloting 第三人称单数: pilots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bond', '[bɑːnd]', 'n.债券；结合；协定；联系；情谊；黏合剂 vt.使结合；为 ... 作保 vi.连结；粘合', '1. An industrial firm issues bond to collect money and will pay back with interest. 工厂发行债券集资并偿还利息。 2. Marriage should be a permanent bond. 婚姻应该是永恒的结合。 3. We entered into a solemn bond. 我们缔结了一项正式协定。 4. Common interests formed a bond between us. 共同的利益把我们联系在一起。 5. The company refused to bond a former criminal. 这家公司拒绝为一个前科罪犯作保。 6. I use water resistant adhesive to get the best bond possible. 我使用防水粘合剂，以获得最佳连结性。', '形容词: bondable 名词: bonder 过去式: bonded 过去分词: bonded 现在分词: bonding 第三人称单数: bonds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('menial', '[\'miːniəl]', 'adj.适合仆人做的；卑微的 n.佣人；家仆；卑贱的人', '1. he performed the menial chore of shining shoes. 他像仆人一样做些擦鞋的家务活。 2. There are no menial jobs, only menial attitudes. 没有卑贱的工作,只有卑贱的态度。 3. There is a positive attitude here, from the boss down to the lowliest menial. 在这里上至老板下至最低微的下人，都有很积极的态度。', '副词: menially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('atomic', '[ə\'tɑːmɪk]', 'adj.原子的', '1. The ship was sunk by an atomic submarine. 这艘船是被一艘核潜艇击沉的。 2. The Second World War brought the atomic bomb into being. 第二次世界大战使原子弹产生。 3. The atomic explosion is always accompanied by huge fireball. 原子弹爆炸总是伴随着巨大的火球。 4. Our first atomic reactor was built in 1958. 我们第一个原子反应堆建于1958年。', '副词: atomically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('negotiation', '[nɪˌɡoʊʃi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.谈判；协商', '1. We are satisfied with the smoothness of the negotiation. 我们对谈判的顺利进行很满意。 2. Their negotiation was fruitless. 他们的谈判没有结果。 3. Price is a matter of negotiation. 价格是可以协商的。 4. The issue is still under negotiation. 这个问题还在商讨之中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('warehouse', '[\'werhaʊs]', 'n.仓库 vt.存入仓库', '1. They stored their goods in a warehouse. 他们把货物储存在一个仓库里。 2. They operate three factories and a huge warehouse. 他们经营三家工厂和一个大仓库。 3. If necessary, please warehouse the goods. 如有必要，请将该货存入仓库。', '名词: warehouser 过去式: warehoused 过去分词: warehoused 现在分词: warehousing 第三人称单数: warehouses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('presumptuous', '[prɪ\'zʌmptʃuəs]', 'adj.放肆的；冒昧的；自以为是的；自作主张的', '1. It is too presumptuous of him to do so. 他这样做太放肆了。 2. I dislike that presumptuous young man. 我不喜欢那个自以为是的年轻人。 3. He was presumptuous in making the announcement before the decision had been approved. 决议尚未通过他已径自宣布。', '副词: presumptuously 名词: presumptuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crow', '[kroʊ]', 'n.乌鸦；啼叫；欢叫 v.报晓；啼叫；欢叫；夸口；洋洋自得', '1. The crow is a bird of ill omen. 乌鸦是不祥的预兆。 2. He gets up at the crow of the rooster every day. 他每天鸡鸣即起。 3. It was dawn, and I could hear a cock crowing somewhere. 天亮了,我听到从某处传来雄鸡的报晓声。 4. The rooster flew up to a big rock and began to crow. 公鸡飞上大石头,开始鸣叫。', '过去式: crowed 过去分词: crowed 现在分词: crowing 第三人称单数: crows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prodigal', '[\'prɑːdɪɡl]', 'adj.挥霍的；(物产等)丰富的；慷慨的 n.挥霍者', '1. I hate the prodigal administration. 我痛恨铺张浪费的行政机关。 2. They are prodigal in their expenditures. 他们挥霍无度。 3. Destinies are very fatal for several and too prodigal or too protecting for others. 对于一部分人，命运是残酷无晴的，而对于另一部分人，又过于慷慨或过于爱护。 4. The prodigal handouts should continue 这些慷慨的施舍必须继续下去。 5. Those prodigals were put into prison. 那些挥霍者被关进监狱。', '副词: prodigally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('twig', '[twɪɡ]', 'n.小枝；嫩枝 v.理解；领悟', '1. Elaine plucked a twig from the offending japonica and set about its systematic defoliation with savage concentration. 埃莱恩从难看的山茶上折了个嫩枝，开始猛烈的收集系统的落叶。', '过去式: twigged 过去分词: twigged 现在分词: twigging 第三人称单数: twigs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amateur', '[\'æmətər]', 'n.外行；业余爱好者 adj.业余（爱好者）的', '1. An amateur shouldn\'t play roulette for high stakes. 外行不该下大赌注赌轮盘赌。 2. You\'re a professional, but I am an amateur. 你是专业的,而我是业余的。 3. Don\'t let yourself be beaten by an amateur. 不要让自己给一个业余运动员打败了。 4. He is an amateur photographer. 他是个业余摄影爱好者。', '名词: amateurism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incipient', '[ɪn\'sɪpiənt]', 'adj.起初的；初期的', '1. There are signs of incipient labour market weakness. 有迹象表明，就业市场初显疲软之态。 2. Regulators are already acting to head off incipient problems. 监管部门已经开始行动，将问题消灭在萌芽阶段。 3. She felt for him an incipient tenderness, but scarcely any passion. 她对他的好感只是一种刚刚萌芽的柔情，还根本谈不上什么爱情。 4. What we see then is an incipient global inflation. 我们看到的是初期阶段的全球通胀。', '副词: incipiently 名词: incipiency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dramatic', '[drə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.戏剧性的；引人注目的；给人深刻印象的；激动人心的 dramatics: n.；戏剧作品；戏剧艺术；戏剧性的行为', '1. After a dramatic pause, the lawyer finished her summation. 在戏剧性的沉默之后,这位律师作完了她的总述。 2. Her opening words were dramatic. 她的开场白十分动听。 3. It was really a dramatic game. 那确实是场给人印象深刻比赛。 4. She made a dramatic speech at the meeting. 她在会上发表了激动人心的演说。 5. Shakespeare\'s dramatics is very popular among the young people. 莎士比亚的戏剧作品在年轻人中很流行。', '副词: dramatically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impulse', '[\'ɪmpʌls]', 'n.冲动；心血来潮；神经冲动；[物]冲量；[电]脉冲 vt.推动', '1. He bought the house on an impulse. 他凭一时冲动买下了这所房子。 2. We were seized by a sudden impulse to run. 我们身不由己突然想跑。 3. On impulse, I picked up the phone and rang my sister in Australia. 我一时心血来潮，拿起话筒就给在澳大利亚的妹妹打了个电话。 4. He had a sudden impulse to stand up and sing. 他突然心血来潮，想站起来歌唱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strike', '[straɪk]', 'n.罢工；打击；殴打 v.打；撞；罢工；划燃', '1. The dockers are coming out on strike for higher wages. 码头工人将举行罢工要求增加工资。 2. The coalminers have been out on strike for several weeks now. 煤矿工人已罢工了几个星期。 3. The strike has delivered a heavy blow to the management. 这场罢工给资方以一个沉重打击。 4. His spirits sagged after that strike. 受到打击后他有点萎靡不振了。 5. He offered to strike the boy with his cane. 他威胁要用手杖打那个男孩。', '过去式: struck 过去分词: struck/stricken 现在分词: striking 第三人称单数: strikes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('atheism', '[\'eɪθiɪzəm]', 'n.无神论；不信神', '1. Inclined to atheism. 倾向无神论的', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('capacity', '[kə\'pæsəti]', 'n.容量；容积；能力；职位；资格', '1. That bowl has a capacity of two pints. 那只碗的容量有两品脱。 2. What is the capacity of this jug? 这个水壶的容积多大? 3. He has a great capacity for learning languages. 他学语言的能力很强。 4. China\'s grain production capacity has improved. 中国的粮食生产能力提高了。', '名词复数: capacities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mode', '[moʊd]', 'n.方式；模式；样式；风格', '1. The country girl was not used to their lavish mode of living. 这个乡下姑娘不习惯他们奢侈的生活方式。 2. The spacecraft was in its recovery mode. 这艘飞船处于返回状态。 3. Her new dress is the latest mode in this season. 她的新连衣裙是这一季最新的款式。 4. He has no intention of changing his mode of attire. 他没有意愿去改变自己穿着的风格。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entice', '[ɪn\'taɪs]', 'v.诱使；引诱', '1. The promise of higher pay enticed me into the new job. 高薪诱使我从事了这个新工作。 2. Nothing will entice the children from television. 没有任何东西能把孩子们从电视机前诱开。 3. The boy was enticed into playing truant. 这个男孩被引诱逃学。', '副词: enticingly 名词: enticement 过去式: enticed 过去分词: enticed 现在分词: enticing 第三人称单数: entices');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deceit', '[dɪ\'siːt]', 'n.欺骗；诡计；不诚实', '1. She told him of his old mother\'s deceit. 她向他诉说了母后的欺骗行为。 2. Deceit is a gift, but vengeance is swift. 欺骗可能会获得短暂的利益，但报复也会迅速地随之而来。 3. He was enmeshed in a web of deceit and lies. 他陷入充满诡计和谎言的圈套。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('besiege', '[bɪ\'siːdʒ]', 'v.围攻；包围', '1. When they came to besiege Kir Haraseth, Mesha did an abominable thing. 当他们来围攻吉珥哈列设时，米沙做了一件可憎的事。 2. The city was besieged by the enemy for a few days. 这座城市被敌人围困了几天。', '名词: besiegement 过去式: besieged 过去分词: besieged 现在分词: besieging 第三人称单数: besieges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('warily', '[\'weərəli]', 'adv.留心地；谨慎地；警惕地', '1. I did not listen to his words warily. 我没有留心听他说话。 2. The travelers edged warily along the narrow road. 旅游者沿着狭窄的小路小心前行。 3. I watched his reaction warily, expecting more of the fury I\'d seen at his house. 我谨慎地看着他的反应,期待着更多的愤怒。 4. The cats, for their part, regarded the chicken warily. 猫们则警惕地看着鸡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('siege', '[siːdʒ]', 'n.包围；围攻', '1. The town was forced to yield after a long siege. 该城受长期围困而被迫弃守。 2. He was smitten with Mary\'s attractions and laid siege to her heart. 他被玛丽的魅力迷惑，对她苦缠不休。 3. The citizens sallied out in an attempt to break the siege. 市民们进行突击，试图冲破包围。 4. He captained the siege of Berlin. 他指挥了围攻柏林的战役。', '过去式: sieged 过去分词: sieged 现在分词: sieging 第三人称单数: sieges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stingy', '[\'stɪndʒi]', 'adj.吝啬的；小气的', '1. After the death of his stingy wife,Edward loosened up a great deal. 爱德华在吝啬的妻子死后，用钱广大方得多了。 2. There was once a very poor person who was also very stingy. 有一个很穷又很吝啬的人向上帝祷告。 3. Since when have you been so stingy? 你是什么时候变得这样小气的？ 4. Although I don\'t like wasting money,I either cannot accept the strict budgeting and stingy man. 虽然我不爱乱花钱，但也接受不了精打细算，小气的男人。', '副词: stingily 比较级: stingier 最高级: stingiest 名词: stinginess');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('identify', '[aɪ\'dentɪfaɪ]', 'vt.鉴定；识别，辨认出，认出；认明；把…看成一样 vi.认同；感同身受', '1. Identify how the incident occurred. 鉴定事故如何出现。 2. The test can identify the presence of abnormalities in the unborn child. 这项化验能鉴定胎儿是否有不正常现象。 3. The markings are so blurred that it is difficult to identify. 标记模糊不清，难以识别。 4. Please identify the registered trademark. 请认明注册商标。 5. I found it hard to identify with any of the characters in the film. 我对这部影片里的任何角色都难以认同。', '形容词: identifiable 副词: identifiably 名词: identifier 过去式: identified 过去分词: identified 现在分词: identifying 第三人称单数: identifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dubious', '[\'duːbiəs]', 'adj.怀疑的；可疑的；不确定的', '1. I feel dubious about his honesty. 我对他的诚实表示怀疑。 2. I am dubious about accepting the offer of the job. 我犹豫不定是否接受提供给我的那份工作。 3. I remain dubious about her motives. 我对她的动机仍存疑念。 4. The testimony given by him is dubious. 他所作的证据是可疑的。', '副词: dubiously 名词: dubiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('civilian', '[sə\'vɪljən]', 'adj.平民的 n.罗马法专家；平民', '1. He resigned his commission to take up a civilian job. 他辞去军职而从事平民工作。 2. People are indignant by their shooting of innocent civilians. 对于他们枪杀无辜平民，人们感到义愤填膺。 3. A civilian was killed by a stray bullet. 一个平民被流弹打死。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reproduce', '[ˌriːprə\'duːs]', 'v.再生；复制；生殖', '1. Lobsters can reproduce a lost limb. 龙虾能使失去的肢体重新再生出来。 2. Some animals can reproduce lost parts of their bodies. 有些动物能再生身体上失去的部分。 3. This copier can reproduce colour photographs. 这台复印机可复制彩色照片。 4. We shall reproduce this handbook in full. 我们将把这本手册完整地复制一份。', '形容词: reproducible 名词: reproducer 过去式: reproduced 过去分词: reproduced 现在分词: reproducing 第三人称单数: reproduces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stylish', '[\'staɪlɪʃ]', 'adj.时髦的；流行的；潇洒的', '1. I love to dress my dog in stylish clothes. 我喜欢给我的狗穿上时髦的衣服. 2. She\'s expert at making cheap, but stylish clothes. 她做便宜而时髦的衣服很在行。 3. With excellent reputation, our company intends to bring the best of china from China and creates innovative ideas of stylish tableware. 基于良好的信誉，我们旨在为流行的器型赋予新品位，为客户带来最卓越的瓷器。 4. He is wearing a suit with shoulder straps and doing a stylish dance. 他身穿吊带西裤，跳起舞来非常潇洒。', '副词: stylishly 名词: stylishness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('separate', '[\'sepərət]', 'adj.分开的；不同的；单独的；各自的 v.分开；隔开；区分；分居；脱离 n.分开；抽印本', '1. Can these two definitions be conflated, or must they be kept separate? 这两个定义可以合成一个呢，还是必须分开? 2. I advocate separate classes for students to learn Chinese in different ways. 我建议我们分班授课，让不同的学生以不同的方式学习华文。 3. We don\'t have a separate dining room—the living area is all one. 我们没有单独的饭厅——活动空间都在一处。 4. The house is divided into two living units or residences, usually having separate entrances. 房屋分为两个居住部分,一般具有各自的出口。 5. We\'d better separate the good ones from the bad ones. 我们最好把好的和坏的分开。 6. Nothing can separate them from each other now. 现在什么也不能把他们彼此分开了。', '副词: separately 名词: separateness 过去式: separated 过去分词: separated 现在分词: separating 第三人称单数: separates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('limpid', '[\'lɪmpɪd]', 'adj.清澈的；清晰的', '1. The Li River is limpid with crystal water. 漓江明洁如镜，清澈见底。 2. A limpid stream ran through the little town. 一条清澈的小溪穿过这个小镇。', '副词: limpidly 名词: limpidity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crash', '[kræʃ]', 'v.撞击；坠毁；发出巨响；崩溃；破产；<俚>宿夜 n.轰隆声；猛撞；崩溃；暴跌；垮台；粗布 adj.速成的', '1. He crashed his car into a wall. 他的汽车撞到了墙上。 2. The rocks crashed down onto the car. 岩石轰隆一声砸在汽车上。 3. She was frightened that the plane would crash. 她害怕飞机会坠毁。 4. The plane crashed (into the mountain). 飞机撞毁(在山上)了。 5. The building fell with a crash as loud as thunder. 建筑物轰隆一声倒塌了，声如雷鸣。 6. The project was launched on a crash basis. 此计划作为最优先项目而付诸实施。', '名词: crasher 过去式: crashed 过去分词: crashed 现在分词: crashing 第三人称单数: crashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('testify', '[\'testɪfaɪ]', 'v.作证；证明；声明', '1. He testified that he had not seen the accident. 他作证说他没有看见那次事故。 2. He agreed to testify on behalf of the accused man. 他同意为被告作证。 3. Her actions testify to her good character. 她的行为证明了她的人品是好的。 4. All kinds of human experience testify to the close link between love and fear. 人类的种种经验都证明了爱与怕之间的紧密联系。', '名词: testification 过去式: testified 过去分词: testified 现在分词: testifying 第三人称单数: testifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('armament', '[\'ɑːrməmənt]', 'n.军备；武器；备战', '1. There is a tendency toward increased armament. 有军备增强的趋势。 2. The armament of any of the great power can destroy civilization. 任何大国的军事力量都能摧毁文明世界。 3. The unit has insufficient armament with which to do battle. 这个分队缺少作战的武器装备。 4. The destroyer\'s armament consist of several small cannon, two torpedo tube and a number of anti-craft gun. 驱逐舰上的武器装备包括几门小口径大炮，两个鱼雷发射管与数门高射炮。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scanty', '[\'skænti]', 'adj.缺乏的；不足的；不够的', '1. He is scanty with words. 他沉默寡言。 2. I have only a scanty knowledge of world affairs. 我对于国际事务只是一知半解。 3. The rainfall was rather scanty this month. 这个月的雨量不足。 4. The harvest is rather scanty this year. 今年收成不好。', '副词: scantily 比较级: scantier 最高级: scantiest 名词: scantiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alert', '[ə\'lɜːrt]', 'adj.警觉的；灵敏的 vt.使意识到；警惕 n.警戒；警报', '1. The alert leopard went up to a deer quietly. 警觉的豹子静悄悄地走近一只鹿。 2. Although he\'s over eighty his mind is still remarkably alert. 他虽已年过八十，但头脑仍然十分机敏。 3. I must alert him to the need to solve the problem. 我必须使他认识到解决这问题的必要性。 4. But we must remain on the alert. 但是我们现在仍然要保持警惕。 5. Troops are on the alert against any possible aggression. 军队戒备着可能的来犯。', '过去式: alerted 过去分词: alerted 现在分词: alerting 第三人称单数: alerts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('granular', '[\'ɡrænjələr]', 'adj.由小粒而成的；粒状的', '1. She embraced the post and forced her head upward beside it, scraping one cheek on the granular ice and the other on the wood. 她紧抱柱子，把头靠上去用力往上顶去，有一边的脸颊被融成粗粒状的冰层边缘划伤了。', '副词: granularly 名词: granularity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dawn', '[dɔːn]', 'n.黎明；曙光；开端；破晓 vi.开始出现；破晓；逐渐明白', '1. We set sail at dawn and headed for New York. 我们在黎明起程，直驶纽约。 2. Diana aroused them just before dawn. 戴安娜在黎明前唤醒了他们。 3. I can see the dawn of the better day for humanity. 我已经看到了人类美好日子的曙光。 4. The sky was pink with the first glimmer of the dawn. 天空因第一丝曙光而呈淡红色。 5. A new era is dawning. 一个新的时代开始出现了。', '过去式: dawned 过去分词: dawned 现在分词: dawning 第三人称单数: dawns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sequence', '[\'siːkwəns]', 'n.顺序；连续；次序；一系列 vt.按顺序排好', '1. We will deal with events in historical sequence. 我们将按照历史上的先后顺序研究这些事件。 2. She made a sequence of dance movements. 她做了一个连续的舞蹈动作。 3. He described the events of that day in sequence. 他按先后次序描述了那一天发生的种种事件。 4. A sequence of murders had prompted the police to actions. 一连串的谋杀迫使警方不得不采取行动。 5. Please sequence the names in alphabetical order. 请按字母顺序排列好名单。', '过去式: sequenced 过去分词: sequenced 现在分词: sequencing 第三人称单数: sequences');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solar', '[\'soʊlər]', 'adj.太阳的；太阳能的', '1. The sun is the center of our solar system. 太阳是太阳系的中心 2. Solar irradiance decreases towards the poles. 太阳辐照率向两极递减。 3. The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy. 太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。 4. The artificial heart is operated from solar cells. 人工心脏是由太阳能电池驱动的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('propriety', '[prə\'praɪəti]', 'n.适当；正当；得体 (复数）proprieties:礼节； 礼仪.', '1. I doubt the propriety of doing so. 我怀疑这样做是否适当。 2. The students in our school can be admitted propriety by No.1 Middle School. 我校学生中考可被华师一高中部适当优惠录取。 3. In propriety of classification, however, the people of a country are not to be counted in its wealth. 然而，按照正当的分类，一个国家的人民不应算作这个国家的财富。 4. Ellen ignored all things contrary to her ideas of propriety and tried to teach Scarlett to do the same, but with poor success. 对于那些自认为不正当的事情爱伦总是不屑一顾，并且想教导思嘉也这样做，可是没有多大效果。 5. China is a country of courtesy and propriety. 中华民族是个讲究礼仪的国家。', '名词复数: proprieties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obvious', '[\'ɑːbviəs]', 'adj.明显的；显然的', '1. It is obvious that she is very clever. 很明显，她挺聪明。 2. The embassy is an obvious target for terrorist attacks. 大使馆是恐怖分子攻击的明显目标。 3. The merits of the scheme are quite obvious. 该计画的可取之处是相当明显的。 4. All great truths are obvious truths. But no all obvious truths are great truths. 所有伟大的真理都是显而易见的事实,但并非所有显而易见的事实都是伟大的真理。', '副词: obviously 名词: obviousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conflict', '[\'kɑːnflɪkt]', 'n.冲突；战斗；矛盾；斗争 vi.冲突；抵触；争执', '1. Both sides suffered heavy casualties in the border armed conflict. 在这次边界武装冲突中双方都遭到了重大伤亡。 2. He was wounded in the conflict. 他在战斗中负伤。 3. This is an irreconcilable conflict. 这是一个不可调和的矛盾。 4. He\'s got involved in a political conflict he can\'t extricate himself from. 他陷在一场政治斗争中不能脱身。 5. Your interests conflict with mine. 你的利益和我的冲突。', '形容词: conflictive 名词: confliction 过去式: conflicted 过去分词: conflicted 现在分词: conflicting 第三人称单数: conflicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dispatch', '[dɪ\'spætʃ]', 'v.派遣；发送；迅速完成；处死 n.急件；派遣；发送；新闻报道', '1. A messenger was dispatched to take the news to the soldiers at the front. 一名通讯员被派去给前线士兵送消息。 2. We have to ask you to dispatch the consignment immediately. 我们得要求你立即发送该批货物。 3. We soon dispatched the chocolate cake. 我们很快就吃完了那个巧克力蛋糕。 4. The criminal will be dispatched today. 那名罪犯将于今日被处决。 5. I threw the dispatch to him and asked him to take prompt actions. 我把那份急件扔给他,让他立刻采取措施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('downtown', '[ˌdaʊn\'taʊn]', 'n.市中心区；市中心 adj.市中心的', '1. Most of the old buildings in the downtown were plucked down, and new ones erected. 市中心的大部分建筑物都拆掉了，建起了新的房子。 2. A new skyscraper has been put up downtown. 市中心又建起了一座摩天大厦。 3. The family lived far away from downtown. 那家人住在离市中心很远的地方。 4. Most of the old buildings in the downtown were plucked down, and new ones erected. 市中心的大部分建筑物都拆掉了，建起了新的房子。 5. I have an apartment in downtown Manhattan. 我在曼哈顿中心区有一套住房。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outgas', '[aʊt\'gæs]', 'vi.除气(漏气)', '1. Leakage and outgas of dewar vacuum vessel also is analysed. 杜瓦微漏孔和真空室内部材料放气使杜瓦真空度下降。 2. The gas-forming hypotheses are mainly synthetic gas and earth outgas hypotheses. 其成气假说主要有合成气说和地球脱气说。 3. But due to the lower extraction efficiency of the SFC, on one hand, a lot of beam lost, and on other hand, outgas from the surface of the electrostatic deflector is serious because of beam hitting. 但由于SFC的引出效率比较低,只有30%25左右,一方面损失了大量束流,另一方面许多束流损失在引出静电偏转板上,造成了大量出气,破坏了真空,难以维持长期大束流运行。 4. Surface Absorption and Surface Outgas 表面吸附与表面放气', '过去式: outgassed 过去分词: outgassed 现在分词: outgassing 第三人称单数: outgasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('philosophy', '[fə\'lɑːsəfi]', 'n.哲学；哲理', '1. This organization espouses the socialist philosophy. 这个组织支持社会主义哲学。 2. He holds the chair of philosophy at Oxford. 他任牛津大学哲学教授。 3. He regarded it as with profound philosophy. 他认为这里面有深奥的哲理。', '名词复数: philosophies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('applicable', '[ə\'plɪkəbl]', 'adj.合适的；适用的；可应用的', '1. Western notions of human rights are not necessarily applicable in other societies. 西方的人权观念不一定适合其他社会。 2. This section of the law is applicable only to corporations. 这部分法律只适用于公司。 3. This part of the form is not applicable to foreign students. 表格中的这一部分不适用於外国学生. 4. Above rate applicable until further notice. 除非另有通知，上述运费率适用。', '副词: applicably 名词: applicability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prosperity', '[prɑː\'sperəti]', 'n.繁荣；兴旺', '1. The new government ushered in a period of prosperity. 新政府的成立带来了一个繁荣的时期。 2. The empire was on the wane after its period of prosperity. 帝国经过全盛以后逐渐衰落。 3. We hope to have a life of happiness and prosperity. 我们希望拥有成功幸福的生活。 4. Prosperity destroys fools and endangers the wise. 繁荣兴旺既毁了蠢人，也使智者陷于险境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wring', '[rɪŋ]', 'v.拧；绞出；拧断（脖子）；使痛苦；强迫取得 n.扭绞', '1. Remember to wring your swimsuit out after you swim. 记住游泳过后要把游泳衣拧干。 2. My socks were so wet that I had to wring them . 我的袜子很湿，我不得不拧干它们。 3. I wrung water from my wet bathing suit. 我把湿游泳衣的水拧出来。 4. I\'ll wring your neck if you don\'t behave. 你如果不规矩点,我就拧断你的脖子。', '过去式: wrung 过去分词: wrung 现在分词: wringing 第三人称单数: wrings');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('literary', '[lɪtəreri]', 'adj.文学的', '1. He is endowed with literary talent. 他有文学天分。 2. Dickens\' A Tale of Two Cities is a literary classic. 狄更斯的《双城记》是文学名著。 3. I don\'t like to read his literary criticism. 我不喜欢读他的文学批评。 4. Her poetry is full of obscure literary allusions. 他的诗里用了很多晦涩的文学典故。', '副词: literarily 名词: literariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('downcast', '[\'daʊnkæst]', 'adj.气馁的；悲哀的；垂下的', '1. The women in the shelter looked at me through downcast eyes. 她们用沮丧的眼神看着我。 2. He seemed very downcast at the news. 那消息似乎使他非常难过。 3. Ashamed of his mistake,he stood with downcast eyes. 羞于他的错误，他眼睛垂视地站着。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nod', '[nɑːd]', 'v.点头；打盹；（使）摆动 n.点头；同意', '1. She nodded when she passed me in the street. 她在街上走过我身旁时向我点了点头。 2. He nodded in agreement with me. 他点头表示同意我的意见。 3. The student began to nod off during math class. 那学生上数学课的时候开始打盹。 4. Trees nod in the wind. 树在风中摇曳。 5. She greeted us with a nod of the head. 她向我们点点头打招呼。', '名词: nodder 过去式: nodded 过去分词: nodded 现在分词: nodding 第三人称单数: nods');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lure', '[lʊr]', 'vt.诱惑；吸引 n.诱惑；吸引力；饵', '1. The travel brochure lured me into taking a Caribbean vacation. 这本旅游小册子诱使我去加勒比地区度假。 2. The enticement of the big city lure her away from her home. 大城市的种种诱惑吸引了她离家出走。 3. It\'s very difficult to lure talent away from Silicon Valley. 很难将硅谷的人才吸引走。 4. Do not lure her away from her duty . 不要引诱她离开职守。 5. He left home because of the lures of the life in the city. 由于受到城市生活的诱惑,他离开了家。', '副词: luringly 名词: lurer 过去式: lured 过去分词: lured 现在分词: luring 第三人称单数: lures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('troupe', '[truːp]', 'n.（演出的）一团；一班 v.巡回演出', '1. The troupe is now on the road. 剧团正在巡回演出。 2. I watched a troupe of travelling actors. 我观看了一个巡回剧团演出。', '过去式: trouped 过去分词: trouped 现在分词: trouping 第三人称单数: troupes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circumference', '[sər\'kʌmfərəns]', 'n.圆周；周围；周长', '1. That point falls on the circumference of the circle. 那一个点落在这圆的圆周线上。 2. He went jogging around the circumference of the reservoir every morning. 他每天早晨绕着水库周围慢跑。 3. This tree has a circumference of 6 feet. 这棵树周长六英尺。 4. The circumference of the earth is almost 25,000 miles. 地球的圆周长约为两万五千英里。', '形容词: circumferential');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('saturation', '[ˌsætʃə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.饱和；饱和度；浸透', '1. So many refugees have arrived that the camps have reached saturation point. 来了那么多的难民,营房都饱和了。 2. The market for computer games has reached saturation point. 电脑游戏市场已达到饱和。 3. I play around with the saturation until I get a pleasing result. 我调整了一下饱和度来达到令自己满意的效果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alternate', '[\'ɔːltərnət]', 'v.交替；轮流 adj.间隔的；轮流的；交替的 n.代替者；供替代的选择', '1. Sunny weather alternated with rain. 天气晴雨相间。 2. One should alternate work and relaxation. 工作和休息应交替进行。 3. We alternate in cleaning the room. 我们轮流打扫房间。 4. Meetings are held on alternate Thursdays. 每隔一个星期的星期四举行一次会议。 5. My alternate knows my role really well, she\'s almost better than me. 我的接替者对我的工作非常了解，她甚至比我都好。', '副词: alternately 名词: alternateness 过去式: alternated 过去分词: alternated 现在分词: alternating 第三人称单数: alternates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clay', '[kleɪ]', 'n.黏土；泥土', '1. Clay is a plastic substance. 黏土是可塑物质。 2. Clay soil retains water. 黏土能保持水分。 3. Bricks and dishes are made from various kinds of clay. 砖和盘子由各种粘土制成。 4. It was said that the first man was moulded from clay by some kind of god. 据传，第一个人是某个神用泥土造出来的。', '形容词: clayey');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('successive', '[sək\'sesɪv]', 'adj.连续的；接连的；接二连三的', '1. We have had three successive years of good harvest. 我们已连续三年丰收。 2. He dropped the nails on the ground and successive clangs were heard. 他把钉子掉到了地上，听见了一连串的叮当声。 3. Continuity is ensured by using the same props in successive scenes. 在连续的场景中使用同样的道具以确保前后衔接。 4. Andrea paid no attention to the successive charges which were brought against him. 安德烈听着维尔福起诉书中接连提出来的罪名。', '副词: successively 名词: successiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prohibitively', '[prəˈhɪbətɪvli]', 'adv.令人望而却步的；（价格）过高的', '1. Car insurance can be prohibitively expensive for young drivers. 汽车保险费有时高得让年轻开车人承受不起。', '形容词: prohibitive 动词: prohibit');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('worldly', '[\'wɜːrldli]', 'adj.世间的；世俗的；善于处世的', '1. When dead, we lose all our worldly possessions. 我们死后就丧失了所有世间的财产。 2. His all worldly possessions amounted to little more than the clothes he stood up in. 他在人世间的他部财产，除了身上所穿的外，别无他物。 3. It simply means to stop doing any worldly work! 停下做世俗的工作的意思。 4. We will never break away from the worldly shackles. 我们永远都无法摆脱世俗的束缚。', '比较级: worldlier 最高级: worldliest 名词: worldliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advance', '[əd\'væns]', 'n.前进；进展；预付金 v.前进；预付；增长；推进 adj.预先的；提前的', '1. Advance in the jungle was very slow. 在丛林中行进很慢。 2. There have been great progresses in medicine in the past decade. 在过去十年里,医学取得了巨大的进步。 3. She asked for an advance on her salary. 她请求预支薪水。 4. The officer directed them to advance. 指挥官命令他们前进。 5. There was no advance warning before the earthquake hit. 地震之前没有任何预兆。', '名词: advancer 过去式: advanced 过去分词: advanced 现在分词: advancing 第三人称单数: advances');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skeptical', '[\'skeptɪkəl]', 'adj.怀疑的', '1. He is skeptical about everything. 他对于一切事都持怀疑的态度。 2. Her tone is skeptical and detached. 她的声音是怀疑的，冷漠的。 3. The leader had the gift of being able to infuse enthusiasm into the most skeptical member of the group. 那位领导人很有天赋，能使团体中最持怀疑态度的人都充满热情。', '副词: skeptically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('innovative', '[\'ɪnəveɪtɪv]', 'adj.创新的；革新的', '1. Its glass carving is beautiful and innovative. 玻璃雕刻创意新颖。 2. These designs are full of innovative ideas. 这些设计富有创新的理念。 3. She was an imaginative and innovative manager. 她是个有想象力和革新精神的经理。 4. This is an innovative approach to language teaching. 这是语言教学中一种革新的方法。', '名词: innovativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drain', '[dreɪn]', 'v.排出；排干；喝光；耗尽 n.下水道；消耗', '1. We must dig a trench to drain away the water. 我们必须挖一条沟排水。 2. They drain the swamp and turn it into fertile land. 他们排干沼泽地的水,将它变成了肥沃的土地。 3. They all rose and drained their glasses. 他们都站了起来,一饮而尽。 4. She felt drained of energy. 她感到精疲力竭。 5. We have to call a plumber to unblock the drain. 我们得叫管工来通一通下水道。', '形容词: drainable 名词: drainer 过去式: drained 过去分词: drained 现在分词: draining 第三人称单数: drains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dispose', '[dɪ\'spoʊz]', 'v.清除；处理掉；解决；杀死；打败', '1. I want to dispose of these old books. 我想处理掉这些旧书。 2. Most complaints can be disposed of pretty quickly. 大多数投诉可以很快地解决。 3. The president ruthlessly disposed of his rivals. 这位总统无情地除掉了政敌。 4. She disposed of the champion in straight sets. 她一盘未输战胜了冠军。', '名词: disposer 过去式: disposed 过去分词: disposed 现在分词: disposing 第三人称单数: disposes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expedite', '[\'ekspədaɪt]', 'vt.加速；加快；有助于', '1. The builders promised to expedite the repairs. 建筑商答应加速修理。 2. We will expedite shipment as much as possible. 我们将尽可能加速装运。 3. Please do what you can to expedite the constuction. 请尽量加快建筑进程。 4. We must expedite the construction of the Southwest area of our country. 我们要加快三线地区的建设进度。', '名词: expediter 过去式: expedited 过去分词: expedited 现在分词: expediting 第三人称单数: expedites');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('censure', '[\'senʃər]', 'n.责难；非难 v.非难；责备；公开谴责', '1. It is not one writer\'s business to censure others. 一个作家的职责并不是去责难其他的作家。 2. In the past, her outspokenness has brought her censure as well as praise. 过去田中真纪子的直言不讳使她在受到褒奖的同时也大受责难。 3. Censure is the tax a man paid to the public for being eminent. 非难是一个人出名向公众付出的代价。 4. Some women had wildly adored him, and for his sake had braved all social censure. 有一些疯狂崇拜他的妇女，为了他甘受社会上的各种非难。 5. Censure is the tax a man paid to the public for being eminent. 非难是一个人出名向公众付出的代价。', '名词: censurer 过去式: censured 过去分词: censured 现在分词: censuring 第三人称单数: censures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('practically', '[\'præktɪkli]', 'adv.实际上；几乎；简直', '1. Bread was practically non-existent. 实际上没有面包。 2. Practically, the plan didn\'t work well. 实际上该计划进行得不顺利。 3. He is practically ruined. 他几乎破产了。 4. The town was practically deserted. 该镇几乎已空无一人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tenant', '[\'tenənt]', 'n.房客；佃户；承租人；<律>占用者 vt.租赁；租借', '1. The tenant has not yet paid his rent. 房客还没有交付租金。 2. The desk was left by the previous tenant. 这张桌子是前面房客留下的。 3. He\'s a tenant farmer. 他是佃农. 4. There is a clause in the contract forbidding tenant to sublet. 合同中列有条款，禁止承租人转租。 5. I will tenant my building out during the summer vocation. 我会在暑假期间把房子租出去。', '过去式: tenanted 过去分词: tenanted 现在分词: tenanting 第三人称单数: tenants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instinct', '[\'ɪnstɪŋkt]', 'n.直觉；本能；天性 adj.充满的', '1. Don\'t trust anything except your instinct. 只管相信你的直觉。 2. She had, too, a true instinct as to the man. 她对这男人还有一种正确的直觉。 3. It is his instinct to reckon on women as constant by their nature. 他的直觉使他认为女人在本质上就是一成不变的。 4. You should not go by instinct in deciding a question. 在决定一个问题时，你不能靠直觉。 5. She likes to hear words instinct with love. 她喜欢听充满爱意的言辞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('depression', '[dɪ\'preʃn]', 'n.沮丧；萧条', '1. He suffers from acute depression. 他患有严重的抑郁症。 2. He committed suicide during a fit of depression. 他一时想不开，自杀了。 3. Many people were idle during the depression. 在那萧条时期，很多人都无事可做。 4. Roughly speaking, I think we are heading for the depression. 大体说来,我认为我们正走向萧条。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insular', '[\'ɪnsələr]', 'adj.岛的；岛民的；岛特有的；与世隔绝的；保守的', '1. A continental climate is different from an insular one. 大陆性气候不同于岛屿气候。 2. The British caricature themselves as a nation of insular xenophobes. 英国人自嘲为惧怕外族、与世隔绝的民族。 3. They are insular--and proud of it. 他们保守，并对此感到自豪。', '副词: insularly 名词: insularism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resist', '[rɪ\'zɪst]', 'v.抵制；抵抗；反抗；忍住 n.防蚀涂层', '1. Many young people could not resist the spiritual pollution. 很多年轻人不能抵制精神污染。 2. They are determined to resist invasion. 他们决定抵抗入侵。 3. The nobility usually resist social changes. 贵族通常反对社会变革。 4. They were powerless to resist. 他们无力反抗。', '名词: resister 过去式: resisted 过去分词: resisted 现在分词: resisting 第三人称单数: resists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prehistoric', '[ˌpriːhɪ\'stɔːrɪk]', 'adj.史前的；陈腐的 =prehistorical.', '1. Some prehistoric people lived in caves. 有些史前时期的人住在洞穴里。 2. They have found prehistoric remains. 他们发现了史前遗迹。 3. His ideas on morals are really prehistoric. 他的道德观念真是太陈腐了。', '副词: prehistorically 异体字: prehistorical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cascara', '[kæs\'kerə]', 'n.鼠李；用其树皮制成的缓泻剂', '1. Costive one tabloid of cascara sagrada. 便秘嘛，请服一片药鼠李皮。 2. A buckthorn(Rhamnus purshiana) native to northwest North America,the bark of which is the source of cascara sagrada. 药鼠李树原产北美洲西北部的一种药鼠李树（珀希鼠李鼠李属），其树皮是药鼠李皮剂的原料。 3. Definition: Cascara consists of the dried, whole or fragmented bark of Rhamnus purshianus D. 本品为鼠李科植物珀希鼠李Rhamnus purshianus D. 4. Cascara supports healthy bowel function by stimulating bowel reflexes to prevent constipation &ensure elimination. 鼠李皮粉可刺激肠蠕动;从而预防和消除便秘;维护正常的肠功能.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aristocrat', '[ə\'rɪstəkræt]', 'n.贵族；有贵族气派的人', '1. He put on the air of an aristocrat. 他摆出一副贵族的架势。 2. Her father was an English aristocrat. 她的父亲曾是英国贵族。 3. He is an aristocrat to the very marrow of his bones. 他是一个道道地地的贵族。 4. Further up, I ran into a man dressed like an aristocrat. 我继续往上走，碰到了一位穿戴雷同贵族的汉子。', '形容词: aristocratic 副词: aristocratically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hieratic', '[\'haɪə\'rætɪk]', 'adj.僧侣的；僧侣用的；手写草书体的；神圣风格的', '1. The Petrie Papyri Hieratic Papyri from Kahun and ... 在仪式里进行割包皮活动）、关于食物的法律（禁止猪 ... 2. Of, relating to, or written in the simplified form of ancient Egyptian hieratic writing. （古埃及）通俗文字的古埃及象形文字的简单书写体的，或与之有关的，或用之书写的 3. Of,relating to,or written in the simplified form of ancient Egyptian hieratic writing. （古埃及）通俗文字的古埃及象形文字的简单书写体的，或与之有关的，或用之书写的 4. A few male figurines in hieratic (sacerdotal) poses and one apparently in a dancing posture may represent deities. 少数几个男性小雕像以僧侣（祭司）姿态出现，其中一个很显然是以跳舞的姿态来表现出神性。', '副词: hieratically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tilted', '[tɪltɪd]', 'adj.倾斜的；成角度的 动词tilt过去式和过去分词.', '1. It is also tilted towards family immigration. 并且是向全家移民倾斜的。 2. Market focus has long tilted to the mean. 市场重心有向多头倾斜的意思。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('punch', '[pʌntʃ]', 'vt.按(键)；以拳重击；开洞；剪票 n.殴打 n.打洞器；钻孔机 n.感染力 n.（酒、水、糖等制成的)鸡尾酒', '1. If you punch in the wrong code, the alarm sounds. 如果你按错了代码,警示器就会响起来。 2. He punched the policeman on the nose and was arrested. 他猛击那个警察的鼻子，结果被逮捕了。 3. The conductor punched his bus ticket. 售票员用剪票夹在他的汽车票上打孔。 4. The punch stunned me for a moment. 那一拳把我打得昏了一阵。 5. Many British movies lack emotional punch. 很多英国电影缺乏感染力。 6. Sometimes even a bowl of fruit punch could make people drunk. 有时候即使一碗水果鸡尾酒,人们也可能会喝醉。', '形容词: punchless 过去式: punched 过去分词: punched 现在分词: punching 第三人称单数: punches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('motor', '[\'moʊtər]', 'n.马达；发动机；机动车 adj.机动的；汽车的；运动神经的', '1. At six o\'clock the motor started up. 6点钟时马达开动起来。 2. If the battery is dead, the motor won\'t turn over. 电池要是用完了，马达就转不起来了。 3. We switched off the motor and started to drift (along). 我们关闭发动机开始滑行。 4. I stopped the car but left the motor ticking over. 我停住汽车，让发动机空转。 5. Last year was really bad for the motor industry in Europe. 去年，欧洲的机动车市场很不景气。', '过去式: motored 过去分词: motored 现在分词: motoring 第三人称单数: motors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jelly', '[\'dʒeli]', 'n.果冻；胶状物 vi.结冻；做果冻 vt.使结冻', '1. The jelly plopped into the dish. 果冻啪的一声落到碟里。 2. Apple jelly is the little girl\'s favorite. 苹果冻是这个小女孩最喜欢的。 3. I can\'t stop humming that awful jelly jingle. 我忍不住常哼那支难听的果冻广告歌。 4. You won\'t get a good set if you put too much water in the jelly. 果冻搀水太多就凝固不好了。', '名词复数: jellies 过去式: jellied 过去分词: jellied 现在分词: jellying 第三人称单数: jellies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stocky', '[\'stɑːki]', 'adj.矮胖的；健壮结实的', '1. Beethoven is a short , stocky man, untidily dressed , with dark and piercing eyes. 贝多芬身材粗短结实，不修边幅，有一双黑色敏锐的眼睛。 2. In the stern is a stocky man dressed in a simple white tunic. 船尾上站着一名健壮的身着朴素白衫的男子。', '副词: stockily 比较级: stockier 最高级: stockiest 名词: stockiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('henceforth', '[ˌhens\'fɔːrθ]', 'adv.今后，此后', '1. The man said that he would work hard henceforth. 那人说从今以后他要努力工作了。 2. Henceforth it will be more difficult to avoid customs examination. 从此以后，避免海关检查将会更加困难。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('startling', '[\'stɑːrtlɪŋ]', 'adj.惊人的 动词startle的现在分词.', '1. He describes the scene with startling reality. 他对那景象的描述逼真得令人惊讶。 2. There fell upon my ears a most startling scream. 我听到一声非常可怕的尖叫。 3. The new hair do effected a startling change in her appearance. 新发型使她的容貌产生了惊人的变化。 4. The results were quite startling -- a 77% increase in six month. 结果非常令人吃惊--六个月增长百分之七十七。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('burglar', '[\'bɜːrɡlər]', 'n.窃贼', '1. The governor pardoned the burglar. 州长赦免了那个窃贼。 2. Did a burglar break into your house last night? 昨晚有个窃贼闯进你家吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irreverent', '[ɪ\'revərənt]', 'adj.不敬的；不逊的；无礼的', '1. He gave her an irreverent reply. 他给她一个不恭敬的答复。 2. She employed an irreverent humor to salt her observation. 她运用玩世不恭的幽默使她的评论更为有趣。 3. It\'s irreverent for a man not to take his hat off in church. 一个人在教堂里不脱帽子是无礼的。', '副词: irreverently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pit', '[pɪt]', 'n.坑；矿井；陷阱；凹痕；(剧院的)正厅后排；（枣）核 vt.使凹陷；使竞争 vi.凹陷', '1. The children were playing in the sand pit. 孩子们在沙坑中玩耍。 2. They dug a pit to bury the rubbish. 他们挖了一个坑把垃圾埋掉。 3. I\'ve got quite used to working in the pit. 在矿井工作我已经很习惯了。 4. When you fall into a pit, you either die or get out. 当你落入陷阱中,不是设法逃出,就是死路一条。 5. The ground was pitted by the heavy rain. 大雨使场地变得坑坑洼洼。', '过去式: pitted 过去分词: pitted 现在分词: pitting 第三人称单数: pits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clarify', '[\'klærəfaɪ]', 'vt.澄清；阐明；净化', '1. These brief remarks may serve to clarify the fact. 这些简要的评论可以澄清事实。 2. The teacher\'s explanation clarified the puzzling problem. 老师的说明澄清了困扰的问题。 3. Would you please clarify your question? 请你把你的问题说清楚好吗？ 4. She asked him to clarify what he meant. 她要他说清楚他是什么意思。', '名词: clarification 过去式: clarified 过去分词: clarified 现在分词: clarifying 第三人称单数: clarifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('publicize', '[\'pʌblɪsaɪz]', 'v.宣传；公布；广告', '1. We should publicize the census well. 我们要做好这次人口普查的宣传工作。 2. We are trying to publicize our products by advertisement on buses. 我们正试图在公共汽车上做广告来宣传我们的产品。 3. No other entity or individual may publicize any major animal epidemic emergency. 其他任何单位和个人不得公布重大动物疫情。 4. To satisfy employees, a firm is likely to publicize bravely its adherence to this policy. 为了稳住职工，公司可能会公布要坚持执行这个政策。', '过去式: publicized 过去分词: publicized 现在分词: publicizing 第三人称单数: publicizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extricate', '[\'ekstrɪkeɪt]', 'v.使解脱；救出', '1. No one could extricate him from difficulty. 没有人能够使他从困难中摆脱出来。 2. Developers can extricate itself from the long-term maintenance. 开发商也可从长期维修中解脱出来。 3. The bird had to be extricated from the netting. 要把小鸟从网中救出。 4. They managed to extricate the pilot from the tangled control panel. 他们设法把困在控制盘里的飞行员救了出来。', '形容词: extricable 名词: extrication 过去式: extricated 过去分词: extricated 现在分词: extricating 第三人称单数: extricates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('loath', '[loʊθ]', 'adj.不愿意的；勉强的 =loathe；loth.', '1. I loath to go with him. 我不愿和他一起去。 2. She seemed somewhat loath to depart. 她似乎不愿意离开。 3. He is loath to get out of bed on cold morning. 在寒冷的早晨他讨厌起床。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mantle', '[\'mæntl]', 'n.斗篷；覆盖物；墙的外皮；（汽灯的）纱罩；[地]地幔 v.覆盖；笼罩；脸红', '1. The light loose mantle was thrown over his tunic. 一件轻质宽大的斗蓬披在上衣外面。 2. The earth had donned her mantle of brightest green. 大地披上了苍翠欲滴的绿色斗篷。 3. The mountain was covered with a mantle of snow. 山上覆盖着一层雪。 4. The earth has a core and a mantle around it. 地球的中心是地核，地核的周围是地幔。 5. Snow mantled the hills. 雪覆盖着丘陵。', '过去式: mantled 过去分词: mantled 现在分词: mantling 第三人称单数: mantles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('paralyze', '[\'pærəˌlaɪz]', 'vt. 使 ... 瘫痪； 使目瞪口呆 =paralyse（英）', '1. Otherwise, my dread of criticism can paralyze me. 不然的话，我对批评的恐惧将让我行为瘫痪。 2. Even the smallest slip could permanently paralyze the patient. 即使最小的失误都会导致小朱利安终身瘫痪。', '副词: paralyzingly 名词: paralyzation 过去式: paralyzed 过去分词: paralyzed 现在分词: paralyzing 第三人称单数: paralyzes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('horror', '[\'hɔːrər]', 'n.恐怖；战栗；厌恶；震惊 adj.恐怖的', '1. He was filled with horror at the bad news. 听到这个坏消息，他心里充满恐怖。 2. At the sight of the snake, he drew back in horror. 一瞧见那蛇，他便吓得缩了回来。 3. Her eyes were popping out with horror. 她吓得眼睛都瞪圆了。 4. The news struck him with horror. 那消息使他震惊。 5. That horror film made my blood run cold. 那部恐怖影片使我毛骨悚然。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expertise', '[ˌekspɜːr\'tiːz]', 'n.专门知识；专门技术；专家的意见', '1. He has the expertise in the management of hotels. 他有酒店管理知识。 2. I have no sewing expertise 我没有缝纫方面的知识。 3. We were amazed at his expertise on the ski slopes. 他斜坡滑雪的技能使我们赞叹不已。 4. The company is eager to develop its own expertise in the area of computer programming. 该公司希望能在计算机程序领域开发出自己的专门技术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('state', '[steɪt]', 'n.情形；状态；国家；州；政府 adj.国家的；州的；国事礼仪的 v.陈述；声明；说明；规定', '1. She wept to see him in such a state. 她一见他那种情形簌簌泪下。 2. The house has fallen into a state of neglect. 这所房屋已处于荒废的状态。 3. The head of state was deposed by the army. 国家元首被军队废黜了。 4. Alaska is a state of ample size. 阿拉斯加是个大州。 5. He was wary of telling state secrets. 他小心翼翼以免泄漏国家机密。 6. Please state the facts honestly. 请如实地陈述事实。', '过去式: stated 过去分词: stated 现在分词: stating 第三人称单数: states');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fit', '[fɪt]', 'adj.适宜的；合适的；健康的 v.适合；安装 n.发作；适宜', '1. I don\'t see fit to tell you all my plans. 我认为把所有的计划都告诉你是不适宜的。 2. The soil is fit for cotton planting. 这种土壤适宜种棉花。 3. The room was a fit place for study. 这个房间适宜读书。 4. He could find a fit opportunity to divulge their marriage. 他找到一个合适的机会来宣布他们的婚姻。 5. His endowments are limited, and scarcely fit him for this post. 他的天资有限,不太适合担任这项职务。 6. She had a fit of hysterics and called him some bad names. 她一阵歇斯底里发作，骂了他几句。', '副词: fitly 比较级: fitter 最高级: fittest 名词: fitter 过去式: fitted/fit 过去分词: fitted 现在分词: fitting 第三人称单数: fits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clinic', '[\'klɪnɪk]', 'n.诊所；门诊部；科室', '1. His clinic is near the newly-built railway station. 他的诊所在新建的火车站附近。 2. He is being treated at a private clinic. 他正在私人诊所接受治疗。 3. He will be tested for HIV at the hospital clinic. 他将在医院门诊部接受艾滋病检查。 4. She is attending the antenatal clinic. 她正接受产前检查.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hint', '[hɪnt]', 'n.暗示 v.暗示；示意', '1. There were subtle hints in his letter. 他的信中有些微妙的暗示。 2. I hinted at his imprudence,his folly,but he did not take my hint. 我暗示他的轻率,他的愚蠢,但他没有觉察我的暗示。 3. He did not drop any hint, nor did his secretary. 他没有作任何暗示,他的秘书也没有。 4. The possibility of an early election has been hinted at. 已经有迹象表明可能提前进行选举。', '名词: hinter 过去式: hinted 过去分词: hinted 现在分词: hinting 第三人称单数: hints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('furious', '[\'fjʊriəs]', 'adj.狂怒的；猛烈的', '1. I was annoyed, indeed furious, over what happened. 出了这件事我很不痛快,实际上是愤怒至极。 2. If this news ever reaches her ears, she\'ll be furious. 这个消息万一传到她的耳朵里，她一定得大发雷霆。 3. She maintained a calm exterior, though really she was furious. 在外表上她保持着平静，但实际上她生气极了。 4. After receiving the insulting letter, he became furious. 他收到辱骂信后怒不可遏。', '副词: furiously');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('surgeon', '[\'sɜːrdʒən]', 'n.外科医生', '1. The surgeon has performed the operation. 外科医生做了手术。 2. The surgeon operated on her for appendicitis. 外科医生为她做阑尾切除手术。 3. The surgeon asked him if he felt nervous. 外科医生问他是否感到紧张。 4. He is reputed as the best surgeon in Paris. 他被认为是巴黎最好的外科医生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boost', '[buːst]', 'v.提高；增加；鼓励；举起；为...做宣传 n.增加；推进；鼓励', '1. This new technique will boost food production. 这种新工艺将会提高食品产量。 2. The publication of this book boost my confidence. 这本书的出版增强了我的信心。 3. The change of management has boosted morale throughout the company. 管理层的变更使整个公司士气大振。 4. Boost me up the tree and I\'ll get the apple. 把我托上树,我就能摘到那只苹果了。 5. Last month saw a tremendous boost in sales. 上个月的销售额激增。', '过去式: boosted 过去分词: boosted 现在分词: boosting 第三人称单数: boosts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contrast', '[\'kɑːntræst]', 'n.对比；差别；对照物 v.对比；成对照 n.[计算机] 反差', '1. Black and white shows a striking contrast. 黑和白形成明显的对比。 2. There is a great contrast between good and evil. 善与恶有明显的差别。 3. The little village was a total contrast to San Francisco. 这个小村庄与圣弗朗西斯科形成强烈对照。 4. When you contrast their work records, Julie is clearly more qualified. 对比他们的工作记录,你会发现茱莉更有能力。 5. The microscope image contains contrast effects. 显微镜所成的图像具有反差效应。', '形容词: contrastable 副词: contrastingly 过去式: contrasted 过去分词: contrasted 现在分词: contrasting 第三人称单数: contrasts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elude', '[i\'luːd]', 'vt.逃避；躲避；理解不了；记不起来', '1. The fox eluded the hunters by turning back quickly. 狐狸急转身逃脱了猎人的追逐。 2. The suspect continues to elude the police. 嫌疑犯继续躲避着警察。 3. The revolutionist eluded capture for weeks by hiding underground. 那位革命者为避免被捕在地下躲藏了几个星期。 4. The meaning eludes me. 我摸不透这意思。', '过去式: eluded 过去分词: eluded 现在分词: eluding 第三人称单数: eludes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('predominantly', '[prɪ\'dɑːmɪnəntli]', 'adv.主要地；占优势地；压倒性地', '1. Vancouver is predominantly a service center. 温哥华主要是一个服务中心。 2. In old China, family heads were predominantly men. 旧中国，绝大多数家庭由男人当家。 3. The votes were predominantly in favour of the government. 选票绝大多数是支持政府的。 4. New Zealand is predominantly an English-speaking country. 新西兰是一个英语主导的国家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('restraint', '[rɪ\'streɪnt]', 'n.克制；抑制；束缚', '1. The police appealed to the crowd for restraint. 警方呼吁群众保持克制。 2. Nobody could count on his restraint or rationality. 谁也不能指望他会克制或讲道理的态度。 3. There is still need for profit restraint. 现在仍有必要限制利润。 4. His rage was beyond restraint. 他怒不可遏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('positive', '[\'pɑːzətɪv]', 'adj.积极的；肯定的；明确的；正面的；正数的；阳性的 n.正面；正数；正片；[语]原级', '1. He has a positive attitude towards life. 他对生活持有积极的态度。 2. We regret out inability to let you know anything positive concerning the above firm. 很抱歉，我方无法让您了解上述公司任何肯定的资料。 3. We still don\'t have a positive answer as to how he died. 他究竟是如何死的，我们还未得出明确的答案。 4. These developments will have a positive effect on the stability of our financial market. 这些发展对稳定我们的金融市场会产生正面的作用。 5. The relationship with this supplier is positive. 我与供应商的关系是正面的。', '副词: positively 名词: positiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transcend', '[træn\'send]', 'v.超越；胜过', '1. Humans should always transcend their limits. 人类应该不断超越自己的极限。 2. We can\'t transcend the limitations of the ego. 我们无法超越自我的局限性。 3. They transcend national borders and generations. 它们超越国界及世代。 4. The song of the future must transcend creed. 赞美未来的颂歌一定要胜过这类教条。', '过去式: transcended 过去分词: transcended 现在分词: transcending 第三人称单数: transcends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suffragist', '[\'sʌfrədʒɪst]', 'n.参政权扩大论者；妇女政权论者', '1. Location Criterion Revive Pit - Replaced Enlivened Stone’s Suffragist Beat Powerfulness with a version of Unstable Boom. 股票本金一旦交给公司，就不能再收回，只要公司存在，就永远归公司支配。 2. This set grants neither.Location Criterion Revive Pit - Replaced Enlivened Stone’s Suffragist Beat Powerfulness with a version of Unstable Boom. 之前，她已经在网络的论坛里听说过这条消息，据说呛了孩子的特级月嫂根本不具备带小婴儿的能力。 3. In 1873, suffragist Susan B. Anthony was fined 100 dollars for attempting to vote in the 1872 presidential election (however, the fine was never paid). 1873年，妇女政权论者苏姗B.;安东尼因为试图在1872年总统选举中投票而被处以100美元的罚款（但是罚金没有交） 4. The whole argument with the anti-suffragists，or even the critical suffragist man，is this：that： youcan govern human beings without their consent. 对争取妇女选举权持反对态度的人或持批评意见的人的全部论点只是：你可以统治别人而不必得到他们的同意。', '名词: suffragism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lately', '[\'leɪtli]', 'adv.最近', '1. I haven\'t had enough sleep lately. 最近我睡眠不足。 2. I\'ve not been feeling very well lately. 我最近一直感觉不太好。 3. I haven\'t heard any news from my son lately. 我最近没听到我儿子的任何音讯。 4. Frank has taken up with Lucy lately. 弗兰克最近经常与露西往来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('setting', '[\'setɪŋ]', 'n.背景；环境；镶嵌；安装；放置；（日月的）沉落；[音]乐曲 动词set的现在分词形式.', '1. Our story has its setting in ancient Rome. 我们这个故事的背景是在古罗马。 2. An informal work setting helps to build employee enthusiasm and morale. 不拘形式的工作环境，提高了员工的热情与士气。 3. She liked the diamond itself but not the setting. 她喜欢那颗钻石，但不喜欢它的镶嵌底座。 4. We are setting up a printing press. 我们正在安装一台印刷机。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oblivion', '[ə\'blɪviən]', 'n.遗忘；忘却', '1. Many ancient cities are buried in oblivion. 许多古城都已被遗忘了。 2. They gain a long tenure in office at the price of final oblivion. 他们为了长期执政，得付出最终被遗忘的代价。 3. Only his unexpected resignation had saved him from oblivion. 而也正因为他的突然辞职，才使他没有被人忘却。 4. The history of Holocaust is being headed into oblivion. 大屠杀的历史正渐渐被人们忘却。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infuse', '[ɪn\'fjuːz]', 'vt.注入；使获得；鼓舞；泡制；倾注（液体）', '1. We must infuse new blood into the Party. 我们必须给党注入新鲜血液。 2. They infuse the young people with patriotism. 他们向年轻人灌输爱国主义精神。 3. The news infused the workers with new life. 那条消息使工人获得新的活力。 4. Don\'t drink the tea until it has finished infusing. 等茶泡好后再喝。', '名词: infuser 过去式: infused 过去分词: infused 现在分词: infusing 第三人称单数: infuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ware', '[wer]', 'n.制品；器具；货物', '1. Delft is a blue-and-white ware. 代尔夫特精陶是一种蓝白色的陶器。 2. The shop sells a great variety of porcelain wares. 这家店铺出售品种繁多的瓷器。 3. There are many small wares in the store. 商店里有许多种小百货。 4. The store displays its wares in the window. 商店把各种物品陈列在橱窗内。', '过去式: wared 过去分词: wared 现在分词: waring 第三人称单数: wares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entertain', '[ˌentər\'teɪn]', 'v.娱乐；使有兴趣；招待；考虑；抱有；容纳', '1. We were all entertained by his humorous stories. 他的幽默故事使我们大家都很开心。 2. A teacher should entertain as well as teach. 教师不仅要教书，也要激起学生的兴趣。 3. I like to entertain friends with music and refreshments at home. 我喜欢在家里用音乐和茶点招待朋友。 4. It was futile to entertain such a question. 考虑这样一个问题是没有用的。', '名词: entertainer 过去式: entertained 过去分词: entertained 现在分词: entertaining 第三人称单数: entertains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stereo', '[\'sterioʊ]', 'adj.立体声的；有立体视觉的 n.立体声；固定形象', '1. Who originated the concept of stereo sound? 立体声是谁发明的？ 2. We\'re being deafened by next door\'s stereo. 隔壁的立体声音响要把我们耳朵震聋。 3. This is no time to lash out on a new stereo. 现在不是奢侈花钱买新立体音响的时候。', '名词复数: stereos');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contravene', '[ˌkɒntrə\'viːn]', 'v.违反；相抵触；否定', '1. Her actions contravene the rules. 她的所作所为违反了规定。 2. This evidence contravenes our theory. 这个证据跟我们的理论不相符.', '名词: contravener 过去式: contravened 过去分词: contravened 现在分词: contravening 第三人称单数: contravenes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('carp', '[kɑːrp]', 'n.鲤鱼 vi.吹毛求疵', '1. I like the white carp most. 我最喜欢白色的鲤鱼。 2. They restocked the pond with carp. 他们重新给池塘放了鲤鱼。 3. It would be wise not to carp or criticize . 不吹毛求疵或批评将是明智的。 4. We will not carp at this great writer . 我们不会对这位伟大的作家吹毛求疵。', '名词: carper 名词复数: carp 过去式: carped 过去分词: carped 现在分词: carping 第三人称单数: carps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('poverty', '[\'pɑːvərti]', 'n.贫困；贫乏；劣质', '1. People in this area were ground down by hunger and poverty. 这个地区的人们受着饥饿和贫穷的折磨。 2. The man lived in poverty after his unemployment. 这人失业后就生活在贫困之中。 3. Poverty reduced him to begging. 贫穷迫使他行乞。 4. They were handicapped by (a) poverty of resources. 他们因资源短缺处境窘迫。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('throng', '[θrɔːŋ]', 'n.人群；一大群；大量 v.群集；挤满', '1. A patient throng was waiting in silence. 一大群人耐心地静候着。 2. She had to press through the throng to reach the stage. 她不得不穿过拥挤的人群走上舞台。 3. He was met by a throng of journalists and photographers. 他受到一大群记者和摄影师的迎接。 4. The rapid influx of well-meaning aid agencies that now throng the dusty remnants of Port-au-Prince has contributed to the confusion. 迅速涌入的救援机构出于善心帮助，但大量群集在太子港的废墟之中却是乱上添乱。 5. The rapid influx of well-meaning aid agencies that now throng the dusty remnants of Port-au-Prince has contributed to the confusion. 迅速涌入的救援机构出于善心帮助，但大量群集在太子港的废墟之中却是乱上添乱。', '过去式: thronged 过去分词: thronged 现在分词: thronging 第三人称单数: throngs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feudal', '[\'fjuːdl]', 'adj.封建的；封地的', '1. She lost faith in feudal traditions. 她不再相信封建的老一套了。 2. He lost faith in feudal traditions. 他不再相信封建的老一套了。 3. The feudal barons were cruel to the people. 封建贵族对人民很残酷。 4. The way some landlords treat their tenants today still seems feudal. 今天有些地主仍以近乎封建的方式对待佃户。', '副词: feudally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('penetrate', '[\'penətreɪt]', 'v.渗透；看穿；穿透；了解；（情报人员的）渗透', '1. The mist penetrated into the room. 雾气渗进了室内。 2. The University Chinese training should penetrate the humanity consciousness 大学语文教育应渗透人文精神 3. Honda\'s success in penetrating Western motorcycle markets. 本田公司的成功渗透西方摩托车的市场。 4. Not many people managed to penetrate my disguise. 没有几个人识破我的伪装。', '名词: penetrator 过去式: penetrated 过去分词: penetrated 现在分词: penetrating 第三人称单数: penetrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bound', '[baʊnd]', 'adj.必定的；有义务的；受约束的；装订的 vi.跳；跳跃前进；猛涨 n.跳跃；范围；界限 动词bind的过去式和过去分词形式', '1. It\'s bound to rain soon. 过一会儿肯定会下雨。 2. You are not legally bound to answer these questions. 在法律上，你没有义务非回答这些问题不可。 3. We are bound hand and foot by the contract, so we are unable to help you. 我们受到合同的约束而不能帮你。 4. He bought a bound volume of the magazine. 他买了一本该杂志的合订本。 5. The dog bounded down the hill. 狗跳跃着朝山下跑去。 6. With one bound, he was over the wall. 他纵身一跃就跳过了墙。', '过去式: bounded 过去分词: bounded 现在分词: bounding 第三人称单数: bounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aura', '[\'ɔːrə]', 'n.气氛；氛围；气味；光环；[医]先兆', '1. The woods have an aura of mystery. 林子里有一种神秘的气氛。 2. An aura of defeat pervaded the candidate\'s headquarters. 失败的氛围笼罩着候选者总部。 3. There is an aura of divinity about him. 他有一股神圣不可侵犯的气息。 4. She always seems to have an aura of happiness about her. 她好像总是喜气洋洋的。', '名词复数: auras');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brand', '[brænd]', 'n.烙印；商标；牌子；标记 vt.加污名于；铭记；打烙印', '1. As an author who was in a period when the new and the old interlaced, Cervantes had a brand of two ages inevitably. 作为新旧两个时代交替期的作家,塞万提斯身上不可避免地带有两个时代的烙印。 2. You may personalize the design to match your company\'s existing brand identity and design specifications. 您也可以进行个性化设计,使其符合公司的现有商标与设计规范。 3. The advertising manager may set as a goal for advertising an increase of 15 percent in consumer brand awareness in the next six months. 广告经理确定的目标为:在今后的6个月里，通过广告，提高消费者商标知晓率的15%25。 4. She\'s gone over to a milder brand of cigarettes. 她已改吸另一牌子味道较淡的香烟。 5. Those who have triumphantly withstood such strains may brand his name. 那些成功地经受了严峻考验的人们或许会污辱他的名声。', '名词: brander 过去式: branded 过去分词: branded 现在分词: branding 第三人称单数: brands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opportunity', '[ˌɑːpər\'tuːnəti]', 'n.机会；时机', '1. You must grasp this opportunity. 你必须抓住机会。 2. We should seize the opportunity to counterattack. 现在，我们应乘机反攻。 3. I\'d like to take this opportunity to thank everyone for their hard work on the project. 我愿借此机会感谢每一位为这个项目辛勤工作的人。 4. The opportunity has not yet arrived. 时机尚未成熟。', '名词复数: opportunities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('synthesize', '[\'sɪnθəsaɪz]', 'v.合成；综合', '1. The two elements are synthesized by a chemical process. 这两种元素已经化学合成。 2. Green plants synthesize carbohydrates from carbon dioxide and water. 绿色植物将二氧化碳和水合成碳水化合物。 3. You must synthesize various opinions. 你必须综合各方面的意见。 4. His works synthesize photography, painting and linguistic devices. 他的作品综合了摄影、绘画及语言学的技巧。', '过去式: synthesized 过去分词: synthesized 现在分词: synthesizing 第三人称单数: synthesizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devote', '[dɪ\'voʊt]', 'vt.致力于；奉献给；把...专用于', '1. You must devote your attention to your work. 你必须专心于工作。 2. After he graduated, he continued to devote himself to the research. 毕业以后,他继续潜心于这项研究。 3. He devoted himself entirely to music. 他将一生奉献给了音乐。 4. He started to study ecology and decided to devote his whole life to the science. 他开始研究生态学,并决心将他的一生献身于这门学科。', '名词: devotement 过去式: devoted 过去分词: devoted 现在分词: devoting 第三人称单数: devotes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rear', '[rɪr]', 'adj.后面的；后方的；背面的 n.后部；尾部；后方 v.举起；养育；饲养', '1. You should keep your front and rear lights in good working order. 你应该使你的前后灯保持好的工作状态。 2. A driver can see the road behind him by looking at the rear view mirror. 汽车司机通过反光镜能看到他身后的路。 3. The sun shines through the rear window. 太阳从后窗照射进来。 4. The main entrance is at the rear. 主要入口在后面。 5. The snake reared its head. 那蛇扬起了头。', '名词: rearer 过去式: reared 过去分词: reared 现在分词: rearing 第三人称单数: rears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('volatile', '[\'vɑːlətl]', 'adj.不稳定的；反复无常的；易挥发的 n.挥发物', '1. The political situation is becoming more volatile. 政局变得更加动荡不定。 2. Food and fuel prices are very volatile in a war situation. 在战争环境下,食物和燃料的价格都很不稳定。 3. He has a highly volatile personality. 他有着反复无常的个性。 4. He had a rather volatile temper and can\'t have been easy to live with. 他脾气暴躁,很难相处。', '名词: volatility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nap', '[næp]', 'n.小睡；绒毛；纳普牌 vi.打盹；疏忽', '1. He was aroused from his nap by the doorbell. 他午睡时被门铃吵醒。 2. It\'s my habit to take a nap at noon. 我有个睡午觉的习惯。 3. Father always takes a nap in the afternoon. 父亲下午总要睡个午觉。 4. Every afternoon the baby takes a nap for 2 hours. 每天下午宝宝都要睡两个小时。 5. The old man napped on the porch. 那位老人在走廊上打盹儿。', '过去式: napped 过去分词: napped 现在分词: napping 第三人称单数: naps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genuine', '[\'dʒenjuɪn]', 'adj.真诚的；真正的；真实的；地道的', '1. He has a genuine desire to help us. 他真心诚意地愿意帮助我们。 2. A genuine friend will not desert you in time of adversity. 真正的朋友不会在患难时弃你而去。 3. It appears to be genuine, but I have my suspicions (about it). 这看来好像是真的，不过我(对此)有怀疑。 4. Viewed from the outside, the company seemed genuine. 从外表上看，这家公司倒像是真的。', '副词: genuinely 名词: genuineness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seminar', '[\'semɪnɑːr]', 'n.研讨会；(大学的)研究班', '1. The old professor had presided over a seminar for theoretical physicists. 老教授主持了一次理论物理学家的研讨会。 2. I attended almost every lecture and seminar when I was at college. 我上大学时,几乎每一个讲座和研讨会都去参加。 3. He also told me that your attendance at his tutorial and seminar had was poor. 他还告诉我说你的辅导课和讨论课出勤率不高。 4. He conducted a seminar on learning strategies at our campus last weekend. 上周他在我们学校办了一个有关学习策略的学习班。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exceptional', '[ɪk\'sepʃənl]', 'adj.异常的；例外的；特别的；杰出的', '1. Forestry has advanced with exceptional speed. 植树造林以罕见的速度得到了发展。 2. By no means are these cases exceptional. 这些例子绝不是例外。 3. This weather is exceptional for June. 六月里这样的天气是反常的。 4. We\'ve enjoyed an exceptional run of fine weather recently. 我们这里最近天气好极了。', '副词: exceptionally 名词: exceptionality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trample', '[\'træmpl]', 'n.踩踏 v.践踏；轻视', '1. You do not harvest happiness where you trample it for other people. 践踏别人的幸福就不会收获幸福。 2. For her own purpose, she can trample on other people\'s life! 为了达到目的，不惜践踏他人的生活！', '名词: trampler 过去式: trampled 过去分词: trampled 现在分词: trampling 第三人称单数: tramples');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inquire', '[ɪn\'kwaɪər]', 'vt.询问；查究 vi.询问；查究', '1. We inquired the way of a boy. 我们向一个男孩问路。 2. I shall inquire of him why the train is late. 我要去问他火车为什么晚点。 3. He frowned and determined to inquire thoroughly into the matter. 他把眉头一皱，决计要把事情查究个彻底。 4. I recommend that you inquire about the job. 我建议你打听一下这项工作。', '副词: inquiringly 异体字: enquire 名词: inquirer 过去式: inquired 过去分词: inquired 现在分词: inquiring 第三人称单数: inquires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boundless', '[\'baʊndləs]', 'adj.无限的；无穷的；无边无际的', '1. The masses have boundless creative power. 人民群众有无限的创造力。 2. His boundless generosity moved us deeply. 他的无限的慷慨深深地感动了我们。 3. A fine example has boundless power. 榜样的力量是无穷的。 4. A small boat was drifting on the boundless sea. 在无边无际的海面上漂着一只小船。', '副词: boundlessly 名词: boundlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rugged', '[\'rʌɡɪd]', 'adj.高低不平的；崎岖的；粗犷的；粗鲁的；(人)坚毅的；(气候)严酷的；(声音)刺耳的；坚固耐用的', '1. They walk on the rugged country road. 他们在崎岖不平的乡村小路上走着。 2. The path to glory is always rugged. 通向光荣的道路常常是崎岖的。 3. The mountain path is narrow and rugged. 狭隘的山路崎岖不平。 4. Are rugged good looks really more attractive? 沧桑冷峻的面容更吸引人吗?', '副词: ruggedly 名词: ruggedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gentility', '[dʒen\'tɪləti]', 'n.文雅；出身高贵；有教养', '1. His gentility is purely made up. 他的文雅都是装出来的。 2. He thinks fine clothes are a mark of gentility. 他认为衣著讲究是身分高贵的标志。 3. He took her hand with discreet gentility. 他温文尔雅地牵着她的手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('determination', '[dɪˌtɜːrmɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.决心；测定；规定；(正式)决定；定位', '1. He was utterly ruthless in his determination to succeed. 他下定决心争取成功。 2. Our sales people need determination and drive. 我们的推销人员需要有决心和干劲。 3. The determination of the amount of iron in ore is very important. 矿石中铁含量的测定是很主要的。 4. The determination will aversely affect the outcome of the game. 这个规定将逆转比赛结果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mandatory', '[\'mændətɔːri]', 'adj.法定的；义务的；强制性的；受委托的 n.受托管理者', '1. It\'s mandatory to pay taxes. 缴税是义务性的。 2. Mandatory retirement ages need to go. 强制退休年龄必须废除。 3. Cremation is mandatory in most areas of Guangdong. 火化在广东大部分地区是强制性的。', '名词复数: mandatories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('functional', '[\'fʌŋkʃənl]', 'adj.功能的；实用的；起作用的 n.【数】泛函', '1. What are the functional benefits of the brand? 你的品牌的功能方面的益处是什么? 2. This is a fully functional automaton. 这是一个有全自动功能的机器人。 3. The computer looks compact and functional. 这个计算机看起来小巧而实用. 4. Bathrooms don\'t have to be purely functional. 浴室不必完全只为了实用。', '副词: functionally 名词: functionality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accurate', '[\'ækjərət]', 'adj.准确的；精确的', '1. Hearsay definitely can\'t be regarded as accurate information. 道听途说的决然不能算作很准确的消息。 2. The manager impressed on his office staff the importance of keeping accurate records. 经理让办公室职员认识到做精确记录的重要性。', '副词: accurately 名词: accurateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('console', '[kən\'soʊl]', 'vt.安慰；慰藉 n.仪表盘；操控台；(游戏)平台；落地式支座', '1. I tried to console her, but in vain. 我试着去安慰她，但是无效。 2. He consoled himself with the thought that it might have been worse. 他聊以自慰的是幸亏事情没有更糟。 3. He was beyond my skill to quiet or console! 我可没有那个本事使他安静下来，或者能给他慰藉！ 4. There are many lights and electrical instruments on the computer console. 电脑控制板上有许多小灯和电子设备。', '形容词: consolable 副词: consolingly 名词: consoler 过去式: consoled 过去分词: consoled 现在分词: consoling 第三人称单数: consoles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aim', '[eɪm]', 'n.目标；对准；枪法 vt.瞄准；针对 vi.瞄准；旨在；致力', '1. What is your aim in life? 你的生活目标是什么？ 2. The aim of the policy is the preservation of peace. 这一政策旨在维护和平。 3. Take careful aim at the target before firing. 开火之前仔细瞄准目标。 4. The shooter\'s aim was perfect. 射击者的枪法棒极了 5. The policeman aimed his gun at the fugitive. 警察用枪对准逃犯。 6. You have to aim at the centre of the target. 你得瞄准靶心。', '过去式: aimed 过去分词: aimed 现在分词: aiming 第三人称单数: aims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chop', '[tʃɑːp]', 'v.劈；砍；剁 n.砍；剁；排骨', '1. He chopped in with a sarcastic remark. 他突然插进一句讽刺的话。 2. She chopped the block of wood in two with a single blow. 她一斧头把木块劈成两半。 3. We had to chop a way through the undergrowth. 我们必须在矮树林中劈出一条路来。 4. You\'ve got to chop up the pork before stewing it. 你必须把猪肉剁细后再炖。 5. The hunter cut off the animal\'s head with one chop of an ax. 猎人一斧砍下猎物的头。', '过去式: chopped 过去分词: chopped 现在分词: chopping 第三人称单数: chops');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('layout', '[\'leɪaʊt]', 'n.安排；布局；设计', '1. The designer chooses the layout of reinforcement. 设计者选择钢筋布置。 2. You will be asked to choose your keyboard layout. 将让你选择键盘布局。 3. The designer chooses the layout of reinforcement. 设计者选择钢筋布置。 4. The robbers studied the layout of the bank. 这伙强盗研究了银行的布局。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rebuke', '[rɪ\'bjuːk]', 'v.指责，斥责 n.指责；谴责', '1. She was roundly rebuked for what she had done. 她做出了这种事因而受到严厉的指责。 2. She rebuked him strongly for his negligence. 她严厉斥责他的疏忽。 3. He received a stern rebuke from his superior. 他受到上司的严厉斥责。 4. The teacher delivered a sharp rebuke to the class. 教师尖刻地指责了全班学生。', '过去式: rebuked 过去分词: rebuked 现在分词: rebuking 第三人称单数: rebukes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('temporary', '[\'tempəreri]', 'adj.暂时的；临时的 n.临时工', '1. He suffered a temporary loss of memory. 他暂时丧失了记忆。 2. My love for you is not a temporary madness. 我对你的爱意,并不是暂时的疯狂。 3. The two parties procured a temporary agreement. 双方达成了临时协议。 4. I engaged a young woman as a temporary secretary. 我雇用一位年轻妇女当临时秘书。 5. The boss hired some temporary workers. 老板雇佣了一些临时工。', '副词: temporarily 名词: temporariness 名词复数: temporaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dictate', '[\'dɪkteɪt]', 'vi.听写 vt.口授；规定；决定，影响 n.命令，支配，主宰；指挥；指令', '1. The teacher dictated a passage to the class. 老师给全班同学听写一段文章。 2. He was dictating a letter to his secretary. 他在向秘书口授信稿。 3. He can\'t write but he can dictate. 他不会写但会说。 4. Businessmen often dictate their letters. 商人常口授信稿令人笔录。 5. If I had the dictatorial power in a dictatorship, I will dictate those IT be kept in detention for appearing too pretentious. 我假如拥有独裁政治的专断权，我会命令把她关起来，罪名是外表炫耀做作。', '过去式: dictated 过去分词: dictated 现在分词: dictating 第三人称单数: dictates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enlightenment', '[ɪn\'laɪtnmənt]', 'n.启蒙 n.【佛教】 开悟', '1. That was the Age of Enlightenment. 这就是启蒙时代。 2. A public can only arrive at enlightenment slowly. 大众只能缓慢地达到启蒙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bulletin', '[\'bʊlətɪn]', 'n.公报；期刊；新闻快报；公示 vt.发表；用公告通知', '1. The mid-day bulletin had not mentioned any definite area. 中午的公报没说具体的地点。 2. Here is a letter adapted from DEAR ABBY, Philadelphia Bulletin, March9,1973. 这里摘登一封＇亲爱的爱毕＇的回信，刊登在一九七三年三月九日的＇费城公报＇上。 3. I finally bought the Bulletin of Ordnance Information. 我终于买到了《兵器情报通报》(期刊)。 4. The radio bulletin warned of the typhoon. 收音机新闻快报发布了台风警报。 5. The company bulletined the staff to attend the meeting. 公司用公告通知全体员工参加会议。', '过去式: bulletined 过去分词: bulletined 现在分词: bulletining 第三人称单数: bulletins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abrupt', '[ə\'brʌpt]', 'adj.突然的；唐突的；意外的；陡峭的', '1. The river takes an abrupt bend to the west. 这河突然向西转弯。 2. His speech comes to an abrupt stop. 他的演讲突然停止了。 3. That young man has an abrupt manner. 那个年轻人态度很无礼。 4. His manner of speaking was quite abrupt. 他的说话方式很唐突。', '副词: abruptly 名词: abruptness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rot', '[rɑːt]', 'n.腐烂；腐蚀；败坏；胡话 v.腐烂；使 ... 枯朽；消瘦', '1. Foot rot is an avoidable affiction. 烂蹄病是可以避免的。 2. Rot in the tree trunk caused the tree to fall. 树干的腐烂导致树倒了。 3. The roof timbers were affected by rot and insect attack. 屋顶的木料已经腐朽并遭虫害。 4. We should stop it the minute the rot sets in. 腐败一产生，我们就应立即制止住。 5. This cheap wine will rot your stomach. 这种劣质葡萄喝了会伤胃。', '过去式: rotted 过去分词: rotted 现在分词: rotting 第三人称单数: rots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('response', '[rɪ\'spɑːns]', 'n.反应；回答；响应；答复', '1. The tax cuts produced a favourable response from the public. 税额削减受到了公众的欢迎. 2. I\'m sorry; the correct response is B. 不好意思,正确回答应该是B。 3. There was an enthusiastic response to my suggestions. 我的提议得到了热情的响应。 4. 他提出指控后迅即得到答复。 他提出指控後迅即得到答覆.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disastrous', '[dɪ\'zæstrəs]', 'adj.灾难性的；极糟的', '1. The new system has had a disastrous effect on productivity. 新制度已对生产力造成了灾难性的影响。 2. This environmental effect of this new factory could be disastrous. 这家新工厂给自然环境带来的影响可能是灾难性的。 3. Such a mistake would perhaps lead to disastrous consequences. 这样一种错误可能导致灾难性的后果。 4. The economic position of the country is disastrous. 国家的经济形势非常糟糕。', '副词: disastrously 名词: disastrousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('portable', '[\'pɔːrtəbl]', 'adj.轻便的；手提式的；[计]可移植的 n.便携的东西', '1. The portable device easily knocks down. 这种轻便装置容易拆卸。 2. Portable telephones are very popular nowadays. 现今，移动电话非常普及。 3. She traded her roller-skates for Billy\'s portable radio. 她拿旱冰鞋换了比利的手提收音机。 4. The new portable computers are going like hot cakes. 新的便携式计算机卖得很快。', '副词: portably 名词: portability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('latitude', '[\'lætɪtuːd]', 'n.纬度；自由', '1. The latitude of the island is 30 degrees north. 这个岛的纬度是北纬三十度。 2. Latitude reaches a maximum of 90°at the poles. 两极纬度的最大值为90°。 3. You have a wide latitude to act as you think best. 你拥有自己认为最好的、广泛的行动上的自由。 4. We allow considerable latitude at these hearings. 我们在这种听证会上允许相当大的自由。', '形容词: latitudinal 副词: latitudinally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conserve', '[kən\'sɜːrv]', 'n.蜜饯；果酱 v.保存；保持；节省；用糖保存', '1. This is a recipe for strawberry conserve. 这是制作草莓酱的食谱。 2. I was surprised to find that the strong man liked to eat conserves. 我很惊讶地发现这个强壮的男人喜欢吃蜜饯。 3. This is a recipe for strawberry conserve. 这是制作草莓酱的食谱。 4. We must learn to conserve what remains. 我们必须学会保存那些剩余的资源。', '形容词: conservable 名词: conserver 过去式: conserved 过去分词: conserved 现在分词: conserving 第三人称单数: conserves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pheromone', '[\'ferəmoʊn]', 'n.〈生化〉信息素', '1. The stronger the pheromone signal, the more other ants followed that route. 信息素的信号越强，循迹而来的蚂蚁就越多。 2. Upon contact, the pheromone is sent to sex-specific regions in the female\'s brain. 当接触的时候，信息素被传送到雌鼠大脑里的性别区域。', '形容词: pheromonal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pursue', '[pər\'suː]', 'v.追求；追捕；继续执行；从事', '1. Everyone has the freedom to pursue their dreams. 每个人都有追求各自梦想的自由。 2. The police are pursuing an escaped prisoner. 警方正在追捕一名越狱的逃犯。 3. Let\'s not pursue this argument. 让我们别再继续这个争论了。 4. She wishes to pursue a medical career. 她希望从事医学工作。', '形容词: pursuable 名词: pursuer 过去式: pursued 过去分词: pursued 现在分词: pursuing 第三人称单数: pursues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cafeteria', '[ˌkæfə\'tɪriə]', 'n.自助餐厅', '1. They had their lunch in a cafeteria. 他们在一家自助餐厅吃了午饭。 2. The cafeteria is on the basement level. 自助餐厅在地下一层。 3. I found him work in a cafeteria by chance. 我偶然发现他在一家自助餐厅工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indicate', '[\'ɪndɪkeɪt]', 'v.指示；象征；显示；暗示，预示 v.表明；指明', '1. This is used to indicate the temperature of the enclosure. 这个用来指示壳体的温度。 2. Sword indicates the bearer to a just and generous pursuit of honor and virtue in warlike deeds. 长剑象征剑的佩有者在格斗中具备公正、宽恕的美德。 3. My car\'s gas gauge indicated that there was little gas left. 我车上的汽油表显示剩下的油不多了。 4. His hesitation indicates unwillingness. 他的犹豫表明不愿意。', '形容词: indicatory 过去式: indicated 过去分词: indicated 现在分词: indicating 第三人称单数: indicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scrap', '[skræp]', 'n.碎片；废品；少许；瘦小的人；争斗；打架 v.报废；舍弃；打架', '1. They wrote messages to each other on scraps of paper. 他们用一些碎纸片互传信息。 2. The cars have been broken down for scraps. 那些汽车已经拆掉当废铁。 3. It won\'t make a scrap of difference. 这不会有丝毫的差别。 4. There is not a scrap of truth in what he has said. 他说的话没有半点是真的。 5. I\'ll soon have to scrap this lawn mower,it\'s beyond repair and on its last legs. 不久将不得不把我这台割草机废弃掉，因它已不能修理，即将报废了。', '名词: scrapper 过去式: scrapped 过去分词: scrapped 现在分词: scrapping 第三人称单数: scraps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ascending', '[ə\'sendɪŋ]', 'adj.上升的 动词ascend的现在分词.', '1. Mine hoists are usually operated by the counterbalance of an ascending and a descending car. 矿井升降机通常用一个升车一个落车互相平衡的方法进行操作。', '副词: ascendingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('olfactory', '[ɑːl\'fæktəri]', 'adj.嗅觉的', '1. It arouses their olfactory sense. 这唤起了他们的嗅觉。 2. He is to develop a sensor to substitute for the olfactory abilities of dogs. 克罗克将研制一种传感器用以代替狗的嗅觉功能。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sensitive', '[\'sensətɪv]', 'adj.灵敏的；敏感的；感光的；易受伤害的；善解人意的 n.敏感的人', '1. She\'s got very sensitive hearing, skin, etc. 她的听觉、 触觉等很灵敏。 2. Don\'t be so sensitive and I was not criticizing you. 别那么敏感,我不是在批评你。 3. What food and fruit are sensitive? 哪些食物和水果是感光的？ 4. The film is coated with light sensitive chemicals, which are change by the different shades and colors of light. 胶卷上涂了一层感光的化学物质，这些物质因光的不同色度与颜色而改变。', '副词: sensitively 名词: sensitiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scrub', '[skrʌb]', 'n.用力擦洗；矮树；渺小之物 v.用力擦洗', '1. Give that floor a good hard scrub. 使劲擦洗一下那地板。 2. The country is covered in scrub. 这一地区为矮灌木丛覆盖。 3. We found the animal on a scrub hill. 我们在一个灌木丛生的丘陵上找到这动物。 4. Although she scrubbed the old pot thoroughly, she could not make it look completely clean. 虽然她彻底地用力擦洗那只旧壶，但她无法把它完全洗干净。', '形容词: scrubbable 过去式: scrubbed 过去分词: scrubbed 现在分词: scrubbing 第三人称单数: scrubs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('posterity', '[pɑː\'sterəti]', 'n.后代', '1. His posterity reversed the verdict. 他的后代为他翻案了。 2. You must stop imagining that posterity will vindicate you. 你可别以为后代会给你昭雪沉冤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intrinsic', '[ɪn\'trɪnsɪk]', 'adj.内在的；固有的；本质的', '1. You have a natural and intrinsic talent and skill. 你天生就具备内在的天赋和才能。 2. These difficulties are intrinsic to such a situation 这是这种情势下固然会有的困难。 3. The intrinsic worth of the pen is 30 yuan. 这支钢笔本身价值是30元。', '副词: intrinsically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inception', '[ɪn\'sepʃn]', 'n.开始；起初；取得学位', '1. The inception of the plan was due to him. 计划的开始取决于他。 2. He had been director of the project since its inception. 这项工作从一开始他就是负责人。 3. The programme has been successful since its inception. 这个方案自开始实施以来一直卓有成效。 4. The club has grown rapidly since its inception in 1990. 这个俱乐部自从1990年成立以来发展迅速。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intoxication', '[ɪnˌtɒksɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.喝醉；陶醉；中毒', '1. Let me tell you what intoxication is. 让我来告诉你什么叫陶醉。 2. People exaggerate graphics, such as the unrestrained cry of intoxication. 人物图形夸张，如奔放呐喊之中陶醉。 3. He suffered from serum intoxication. 他得了血清中毒。 4. Caffeine use can lead to a condition called caffeine intoxication. 过多咖啡因摄入可能导致咖啡因中毒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rashly', '[ræʃli]', 'adv.莽撞地；冒失地', '1. There are still a few travellors who rashly attempt to cross the pass on foot. 有些旅行者还是莽撞地企图步行穿过山口。 2. It is said that Sisyphus, being near to death, rashly wanted to test his wife\'s love. 还有人说，西西弗斯在临死前冒失地要检验他妻子对他的爱情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('precious', '[\'preʃəs]', 'adj.宝贵的；珍贵的；矫揉造作的 adv.极其 n.<口>宝贝，心爱的人', '1. You should make good use of every precious minute to study. 你应很好利用宝贵的每一分钟去学习。 2. Pandas are precious creatures. 熊猫是珍贵的动物。 3. That old book is my most precious possession. 那本旧书是我最珍贵的财产。 4. He is a rather precious young man. 他是一个惺惺作态的年轻男子。 5. Precious few people can afford prices like that. 没有什麽人出得起那个价钱。', '副词: preciously 名词: preciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impulsive', '[ɪm\'pʌlsɪv]', 'adj.冲动的；任性的 n.(引起冲动的)原因', '1. Her impulsive passion was a positive defect. 她的冲动的激情则完完全全是个缺点。 2. A jagged equity curve tends to be a sign of impulsive trading. 锯齿状曲线多半代表冲动的交易。', '副词: impulsively 名词: impulsiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strand', '[strænd]', 'n.缕；(线等的)股；海滨，河岸，海滩 v.使陷于困境；弄断；使落后；（使）搁浅', '1. She twirled a strand of hair round her finger. 她把一绺头发卷绕在手指上。 2. One strand of silk doesn\'t make a thread; one tree doesn\'t make a forest. 单丝不成线,独木不成林。', '过去式: stranded 过去分词: stranded 现在分词: stranding 第三人称单数: strands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contend', '[kən\'tend]', 'v.竞争；争斗；争辩；坚决主张', '1. Three armed groups were contending for power. 三个武装集团在争夺权力。 2. John has to contend with great difficulties. 约翰得与那些艰难困苦作斗争。 3. They have to contend against drought every year. 他们每年都得与干旱做斗争。 4. But the potential is simply too significant, the experts contend. 但是专家们主张，潜力是非常重要的。', '名词: contender 过去式: contended 过去分词: contended 现在分词: contending 第三人称单数: contends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fixture', '[\'fɪkstʃər]', 'n.固定物；固定装置；固定成员；【机】夹具', '1. A new fireplace fixture was fixed in the wall. 新的壁炉的固定物被固定在墙上。 2. In America, this kind of computers have become a fixture in offices. 这种电子计算机现在已成为美国各地办公室里的必备之物。 3. The flagpole has been a fixture since the building was first opened a century ago. 这个旗杆从一个世纪前饭店开业起就一直固定在那里。 4. The price includes all fixtures and fittings. 这个价钱把全部固定装置和设备都打在里面了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glamour', '[\'ɡlæmər]', 'n.魔力；魅力 v.迷住', '1. The glamour of inexperience is over your eyes. 无经验的魔力蒙住了你的眼睛。 2. Why did the time really like to murder all the glamour? 为什么时光真的喜欢杀死所有的魔力呢？ 3. A luxuriant tan bespeaks health and glamour. 丰润的棕色皮肤是健康和魅力的标志。 4. Yet Hollywood has not lost all its glamour. 但是，好莱坞还没有完全失去它的魅力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('willful', '[\'wɪlfəl]', 'adj.任性的；故意的；有意的', '1. Yes, I\'ve often been the willful child. 因为我常常表现得和那个任性的孩子一样。 2. A willful beast must go his own way. 任性的野兽一定会坚持走自已的路。', '副词: willfully 名词: willfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decline', '[dɪ\'klaɪn]', 'v.下降；减少；变弱；拒绝；倾斜 n.衰微；跌落；晚年', '1. I wish prices would decline. 但愿物价下降。 2. The price of 14 inches TV set declined from 400 to 320 yuan each. 14英寸的电视机每台从400元降到320元。 3. He spent his declining years in the country. 他在乡间度过晚年。 4. I must regretfully decline your kind invitation. 我很抱歉必须拒绝你的盛情邀请。 5. This decline in vigour with the passing of time is called ageing. 这种随着时间流逝的活力衰退就叫做衰老。', '形容词: declinable 名词: decliner 过去式: declined 过去分词: declined 现在分词: declining 第三人称单数: declines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('haul', '[hɔːl]', 'v.拖；拉；拖运 v.（使船）改变方向 n.拖；拉；搬运', '1. They hauled the boat up the beach. 他们把船拖上岸。 2. It cost him no end of time and groans to haul his wounded leg behind him; 他拖着那条受伤的大腿往上爬，时不时地呻吟一声，速度非常慢。 3. So I won\'t have to haul you around all the time. 这样我就不用老是拉着你去这去那了。 4. Falumpasets haul battle wagons and the catapults of the Gungan Grand Army into the battlefield, and Boss Nass uses a decorated falumpaset as a ceremonial transport. 费隆帕斯特拖运刚耿大军的战车及投石机上战场，而那斯老大以一只装饰华丽的费隆帕斯特做为典礼上用的交通工具。 5. It is a long haul to drive across the country. 开车越过这个国家，是一段艰苦的长途旅行。', '名词: hauler 过去式: hauled 过去分词: hauled 现在分词: hauling 第三人称单数: hauls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prominent', '[\'prɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.显著的；杰出的；突出的', '1. That school is prominent in baseball. 那个学校以棒球著称。 2. Virginia Woolf is one of the most prominent writers in English literature. 弗吉尼亚·尔夫是英国文学史中一名重要的作家。 3. Einstein was a prominent scientist. 爱因斯坦是一位卓越的科学家。 4. She is having a lean, gaunt frame with prominent bones. 他骨瘦如柴的身材又细又瘦,骨骼突出的', '副词: prominently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distillation', '[ˌdɪstɪ\'leɪʃn]', 'n.蒸馏', '1. Purification of water may be achieved by distillation. 水的净化可由蒸馏获得。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gangster', '[\'ɡæŋstər]', 'n.匪徒；歹徒', '1. The gangster was flushed out from his hideout. 匪徒从藏匿处被驱赶出来。 2. He has opened one gun, and has wounded one of the gangster. 他开了一枪，击伤了其中一个匪徒。 3. He looked upon the gangster with hatred. 他以仇视的目光面对着歹徒。 4. The gangster suddenly fished out a dazzling dagger from the bag. 歹徒突然从包中掏出一把亮锃锃的匕首。', '名词: gangsterdom');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subject', '[\'sʌbdʒɪkt]', 'n.话题；科目；主题；题材；主观；[语]主语 n.实验对象；(君主国)国民 adj.易患的；服从的 vt.使服从；使隶属；使遭遇', '1. She dare not mention the subject again. 她不敢重提那个话题。 2. Mathematics is her favorite subject. 数学是她喜欢的科目。 3. He is said to be writing a paper on this subject. 据说他正在写一篇关于这个主题的论文。 4. Hawthorne concedes that normal life can be a subject for art. 霍桑承认日常生活可以作为艺术的题材。 5. We need some male subjects for a psychology experiment. 我们需要几个男子作心理学实验对象。 6. Mary is very subject to colds. 玛丽很容易患感冒。 7. Ancient Rome subjected most of Europe 古罗马帝国征服了欧洲大部分。', '名词: subjection 过去式: subjected 过去分词: subjected 现在分词: subjecting 第三人称单数: subjects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grace', '[ɡreɪs]', 'n.优美；优雅；恩惠 vt.使优美；使荣耀', '1. She performed on the balance beam with much grace. 她在平衡木上表演得非常优美。 2. She was a beautiful girl with the grace and poise of a natural model. 她是一个美丽的姑娘，有着模特儿的那种优雅姿态。 3. By the grace of God their lives were spared. 蒙上帝恩宠 4. Fine paintings graced the walls of the room. 这些精美的绘画使四壁生辉。', '过去式: graced 过去分词: graced 现在分词: gracing 第三人称单数: graces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distinct', '[dɪ\'stɪŋkt]', 'adj.明显的；清晰的；不同的；独特的', '1. There is a distinct possibility that she\'ll be your teacher next term. 她下学期当你们的老师的可能性非常大。 2. On the contrary, he was looking at Harry with distinct pride. 相反,他望着哈利的目光中带着明显的自豪。 3. There\'s a distinct smell of cigarettes every time he comes into the room. 他每次进房间,都带着一股浓重的烟味。 4. Two people may both dream of the other,and find that their dreams had a distinct connection. 两个人可能互相梦见对方,而且发现他们的梦有着清晰的联系。', '副词: distinctly 名词: distinctness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('marital', '[\'mærɪtl]', 'adj.婚姻的', '1. We don\'t know her marital status, whether or not she has children. 我们不清楚她的婚姻状况,也不知道她是否有孩子。 2. We can define marital felicity accurately. 我们能够给美满婚姻下个准确定义。 3. He is faced with the fact of an irremediable marital breakdown. 他面临着不可挽救的婚姻破裂的事实。 4. He did not appear to have any financial or marital problems. 他看起来没有任何经济或婚姻问题。', '副词: maritally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('carbon', '[\'kɑːrbən]', 'n.碳；复写纸；复本；碳精棒', '1. Carbon dioxide consists of carbon and oxygen. 二氧化碳是由碳和氧组成的。 2. He decided to use carbon because it does not melt. 于是，他决定用碳，因为碳不易熔化。 3. I make a carbon copy of my documents. 我用复写纸复写文件。 4. She put the carbon paper in the wrong way round. 他把复写纸放反了。', '形容词: carbonous');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sublimate', '[\'sʌblɪmeɪt]', 'v.使（心灵或物质）升华 n.升华物 adj.升华的；纯净的；高尚的；理想化的', '1. Her sublimate future husband will be tall, dark, and handsome. 她理想化的未来丈夫将是身材高大，皮肤浅黑，相貌英俊。', '过去式: sublimated 过去分词: sublimated 现在分词: sublimating 第三人称单数: sublimates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('realm', '[relm]', 'n.领域；王国', '1. They exist only in the physical realm. 它们只存在于物质感官的领域。 2. He made outstanding contributions in the realm of foreign affairs. 他在外交领域作出了卓越贡献。 3. The material realm is one area that everyone relates to. 物质领域是与每个人有联系的一个地方。 4. He was banished from the realm. 他被驱逐出境。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equitable', '[\'ekwɪtəbl]', 'adj.公平的；公正的', '1. Paying a person what he has earned is equitable. 酬其应得，乃公平之事。 2. We pledge personal respect, fair compensation and honest and equitable treatment. 我们保证尊重个人，提供合理的报酬，真诚而公平的对待每个人。 3. They are always prompt and equitable in settling claims. 他们总是迅速而公正地解决索赔。', '副词: equitably 名词: equitableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infamous', '[\'ɪnfəməs]', 'adj.无耻的；臭名昭著的', '1. I was shocked by her infamous behaviour. 她的无耻行径令我震惊。 2. The king was infamous for his guilt of many infamies. 那个国王因罪恶多端而臭名昭著。 3. That infamous criminal was finally sentenced to death. 那个臭名卓著的罪犯终于被判处死刑。', '副词: infamously 名词: infamousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recreation', '[ˌrekri\'eɪʃn]', 'n.消遣；娱乐', '1. In other words, we had better take sufficient recreation to relax after work. 换句话说，我们最好工作后，消遣消遣来轻松一下。 2. Art is both creation and recreation. 艺术是创作，同时也是消遣。 3. Some films combine education with recreation . 有些影片把教育同娱乐融合在一起。 4. Our city needs more facilities for recreation. 我们城市需要更多的娱乐设施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cohesive', '[koʊ\'hiːsɪv]', 'adj.粘性的；有结合性的；有粘聚性的', '1. I would use a cohesive glue to weld the tubes to each other. 我会用粘胶把这些电子管粘起来。 2. He skillfully fuses these fragments into a cohesive whole. 他巧妙地把这些片断合并成连贯的整体。 3. They do not see themselves as a cohesive group. 他们不认为他们自己是有凝聚力的一群。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consent', '[kən\'sent]', 'n.同意；赞成 v.同意；答应', '1. My father will never give his consent to our marriage. 我父亲决不会同意我们的婚姻的。 2. By the common consent of critics, Shakespeare is the prince of character delineators. 评论家一致公认莎士比亚是刻画人物的大师。 3. Her smile implied her consent to our proposal. 她的微笑暗示她赞成我们的提议。 4. On the other hand, it is not likely that the few landlords from the upper strata of the Miao nationality will consent to their demand. 但是这样的要求，可能苗族上层少数地主分子不赞成。 5. I\'m sure he wouldn\'t consent 我确信他不会同意。', '名词: consenter 过去式: consented 过去分词: consented 现在分词: consenting 第三人称单数: consents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('undertaking', '[ˌʌndər\'teɪkɪŋ]', 'n.事业；企业；保证；许诺；殡仪业', '1. He blazed away at his undertaking. 他全力以赴地工作。 2. He is too timid to venture upon a new undertaking. 他太胆小，不敢从事新的事业。 3. He has sunk half his fortune in a new business undertaking. 他已把一半财产投资于一种新的企业中。 4. The undertaking enterprise may not contract the processing of the processing trade goods to any other enterprise again. 承揽企业不得将加工贸易货物再次外发至其他企业进行加工。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expire', '[ɪk\'spaɪər]', 'vi.终止；期满；失效；呼气；断气', '1. Our holidays expire next week. 我们的假期于下星期结束。 2. My passport is due to expire in two months. 我的护照再过两个月就到期了。 3. When does your driving licence expire? 你的驾驶执照何时到期? 4. My credit card will expire in June. 我的信用卡六月过期。', '过去式: expired 过去分词: expired 现在分词: expiring 第三人称单数: expires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foresight', '[\'fɔːrsaɪt]', 'n.远见；深谋远虑', '1. No one had enough foresight to predict the winner. 谁也没有足够的远见能预测哪一个获胜。 2. The decision they made is a lamentable lack of foresight. 他们做的决定实在缺乏远见。 3. A fool acts recklessly while a wit has a foresight. 愚者鲁莽从事,智者深谋远虑。', '形容词: foresighted 副词: foresightedly 名词: foresightedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intelligence', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒəns]', 'n.智力；理解力 n.情报；情报工作；情报机关', '1. She\'s the equal of her brother as far as intelligence is concerned. 论智力，她和她哥哥不相上下。 2. His intelligence is rather limited. 他的智力相当有限。 3. She\'s not lacking in intelligence. 她并不缺乏学识。 4. Our intelligence shows that the enemy is advancing. 我们的情报显示敌人正在向前推进。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('buffalo', '[\'bʌfəloʊ]', 'n.水牛；野牛；水陆坦克 vt.威吓；欺骗；迷惑', '1. Asian buffalo isn\'t as wild as that of America\'s. 亚洲水牛比美国水牛温顺些。 2. There were lots of buffaloes in the North America 100 years ago. 100年前，北美有大量的野牛。 3. Don\'t buffalo me into doing something I don\'t want to do. 别威胁我做我不想做的事。 4. He tried to buffalo me at first meeting but I soon caught on to his tricks. 初次见面时他企图欺骗我，但是我很快就明白了他耍的花招。', '名词复数: buffalo 过去式: buffaloed 过去分词: buffaloed 现在分词: buffaloing 第三人称单数: buffaloes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('astronomy', '[ə\'strɑːnəmi]', 'n.天文学', '1. Physics and astronomy are cognate sciences. 物理学和天文学是相关联的科学。 2. Astronomy, as distinct from astrology, is an exact science. 天文学是一门严谨的科学，与占星术完全不同。 3. Astronomy is the scientific study of the sun, moon, and stars and other heaven bodies. 天文学是研究太阳、月亮、星星和其他天体的科学。 4. We\'re at cross-purposes: I\'m talking about astronomy, you\'re talking about astrology. 我们彼此误解了: 我谈的是天文学，你谈的是占星术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blade', '[bleɪd]', 'n.刀刃；刀锋；桨叶；叶片', '1. The blade needs sharpening. 这刀刃需要磨一磨。 2. The blade slashed his leg open. 刀刃把他的腿划破了。 3. The blade is chipped in a few places. 刀锋有几个地方缺口。 4. The propellar blade is powered by a diesel engine. 螺旋桨叶由柴油发动机驱动。', '形容词: bladed');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pamphlet', '[\'pæmflət]', 'n.小册子', '1. He gave me a pamphlet for my call numbers. 他给了我一个小册子记录电话号码。 2. The pamphlet was written to his party. 这本小册子是特地为他的政党所写的。', '形容词: pamphletary');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dialect', '[\'daɪəlekt]', 'n.方言；地方话', '1. Every now and then he would lapse into the local dialect. 他讲话中时而不自觉地冒出地方方言。 2. She speaks a dialect, not the Queen\'s English. 她说一口方言，不是标准英语。 3. The dialect is spoken principally in the rural areas. 这种方言主要在农村地区使用。 4. The use of dialect lent great charm to the work . 方言的运用给这部作品增添了巨大的魅力。', '形容词: dialectal 副词: dialectally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fabric', '[\'fæbrɪk]', 'n.结构；织物；构造', '1. The whole fabric of the society was changed by the war. 战争改变了整个社会结构。 2. The cost of repairing the fabric of the church was very high. 修理教堂结构的花费非常大。 3. This fabric has a tear in it. 这织物上有个破洞。 4. The fabric was displayed on a wired stand. 那种织物陈列在金属制的架子上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alien', '[\'eɪliən]', 'n.外侨；外国人；外星人 adj.外国的；陌生的；相异的', '1. Immigrant workers were classed as resident aliens. 移民来的工人已归入外侨类。 2. She is declared an undesirable alien and deport. 她被宣布是不受欢迎的外国人并被驱逐出境。 3. I followed the alien to see where it was to go. 我跟着外星人看它朝哪儿去。 4. I ran into an old friend in the alien land. 我在异国他乡遇到故知。', '过去式: aliened 过去分词: aliened 现在分词: aliening 第三人称单数: aliens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flimsy', '[\'flɪmzi]', 'adj.轻而薄得；易坏的；不足信的 n.复写纸；薄纸副本', '1. She wore a flimsy dress. 她穿一件薄连衣裙。 2. It is a flimsy cardboard box. 那是一个不结实的纸箱。 3. The evidence against him was flimsy. 指控他的证据不足信。 4. A close inspection of this argument would reveal how flimsy it is. 仔细想想这个问题就会发现它其实毫无根据。', '副词: flimsily 比较级: flimsier 最高级: flimsiest 名词: flimsiness 名词复数: flimsies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('raid', '[reɪd]', 'n.突然袭击；突击搜捕；劫掠；集体抛售 v.劫掠；攫取；突击搜捕；袭击', '1. We launched a bombing raid on enemy bases. 我们对敌方基地实施了突然袭击。 2. The raid was purely retaliatory. 这次袭击完全是报复性的。 3. Police made a lightning raid on the house. 警方突然查抄了那座房子。 4. They were arrested during a dawn raid. 在一次清晨的突击搜查中，他们都被捕了。 5. They promise they will never raid tourist. 他们保证再也不抢劫游客。', '名词: raider 过去式: raided 过去分词: raided 现在分词: raiding 第三人称单数: raids');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('posture', '[\'pɑːstʃər]', 'n.姿势；态度；情形 v.作 ... 姿势；摆架子', '1. Only humans have a natural upright posture. 只有人类才有自然直立的姿势。 2. The artist asked his model to take a reclining posture. 画家要求模特取斜倚着的姿势。 3. She has very good posture. 她举止很优雅。 4. The government adopted an uncompromising posture on the issue of independence. 政府在独立的问题上采取了毫不妥协的态度。 5. The war-monger would sometimes posture for peace 战争贩子有时也会装出主张和平的姿态。', '形容词: postural 名词: posturer 过去式: postured 过去分词: postured 现在分词: posturing 第三人称单数: postures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('puppet', '[\'pʌpɪt]', 'n.木偶；傀儡', '1. He jerked the string and the puppet jumped. 他猛地一拉绳子，木偶就跳了起来。 2. How do you work these puppets? 你怎么操作这些木偶呢？ 3. Most kids love puppet shows. 大部分的孩子喜欢木偶节目。 4. Are we the puppets of fate? 我们是听任命运摆布的傀儡吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('moderate', '[\'mɑːdərət]', 'adj.适度的；温和的；稳健的；中等的 v.节制；使 ... 稳定，使 ... 缓和 n.稳健的人', '1. Moderate exercise will be of benefit to you. 适度运动对你有益。 2. Corn plants grow well in moderate weather. 谷类植物在温和气候中生长繁盛。 3. He holds moderate opinions. 他的意见稳健不偏激。 4. The team enjoyed only moderate success last season. 上个赛季，这个球队只取得了中等成绩。 5. She moderated her enthusiasm deliberately . 她有意地节制了自己的热情。 6. He is a moderate. 他是个稳健的人', '副词: moderately 名词: moderateness 过去式: moderated 过去分词: moderated 现在分词: moderating 第三人称单数: moderates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comprehensive', '[ˌkɑːmprɪ\'hensɪv]', 'adj.全面的；广泛的；综合的；理解的', '1. The reporter has made a comprehensive report. 记者已做了全面的报道。 2. She has a comprehensive grasp of the subject. 她已全面掌握了这一学科。 3. Applying the most comprehensive metal is iron. 应用最广泛的金属是铁。 4. We have a rather comprehensive subway system here. 我们这儿有相当广泛的地铁系统。', '副词: comprehensively 名词: comprehensiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('raft', '[ræft]', 'n.筏；木排；救生艇 n.<口>大量 v.乘筏；制成筏', '1. We pulled the oars in unison and the raft slid downstream. 我们一起划桨，筏顺流而下。 2. The raft was floating gently down the river. 筏子顺河水缓缓漂流。 3. We could find no boats around the ferry, and we had to cross the river on a raft. 我们在渡口周围找不到船只,因此我们必须用筏过河。 4. The swimming raft was dancing in the waves. 木排在波浪中浮沉着。 5. They would tie and raft their boats up to have party. 他们将把他们的小船绑在一起，扎成筏子举行聚会。', '过去式: rafted 过去分词: rafted 现在分词: rafting 第三人称单数: rafts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('auspice', '[\'ɔːspɪs]', 'n.预兆；吉兆；赞助；主办', '1. With peace and auspice every of your years. 每一月都是平安吉祥。 2. He took that as an auspice of happiness. 他把那看作是幸福的徵兆。 3. It is the symbol of dignitary, reverence , and auspice. 这是权贵;尊严和吉祥的象征. 4. Jane\'s aunt disliked him very much and had some bad auspice . 简的阿姨非常讨厌他并有一些坏预兆。', '名词复数: auspices');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immigrate', '[\'ɪmɪɡreɪt]', 'v.移居入境', '1. My family and I are planning to immigrate to America next year. I have so many questions. Can you help me? 我的家人和我打算明年移民到美国，我有很多问题，你能帮我忙吗？ 2. People from many countries immigrated to the United States and Canada. 许多国家的人移居到美国和加拿大。', '名词: immigration 过去式: immigrated 过去分词: immigrated 现在分词: immigrating 第三人称单数: immigrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dilate', '[daɪ\'leɪt]', 'v.使扩大；扩大；膨胀；详述', '1. Sometimes, I feel I need to dilate my pupils to remain attentive. 有时,我觉得需要扩大瞳孔才能精神集中。 2. The horse dilated its nostrils. 那匹马张大它的鼻孔。 3. The cat dilated its eyes in the darkness. 猫在黑暗中睁大眼睛。 4. The balloon will dilate with air. 气球充气将会膨胀。', '形容词: dilatable 副词: dilatably 名词: dilatability 过去式: dilated 过去分词: dilated 现在分词: dilating 第三人称单数: dilates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tournament', '[\'tʊrnəmənt]', 'n.锦标赛；比赛；比武', '1. Winning the tournament gratified the golf champion. 那位高尔夫球世界冠军为赢得锦标赛而感到高兴。 2. His victory in the tournament earned him $50000. 他在这次锦标赛中获胜，挣得了5万元。 3. I won the tennis tournament. 我赢了那场网球比赛。 4. She went out in the first round of the tournament/went out of the tournament in the first round. 她在比赛的第一轮比赛中遭淘汰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('special', '[\'speʃl]', 'adj.特别的；特殊的；专门的 n.特别的东西；特刊；特色菜；特价', '1. She is a special friend of mine. 她是我一个特别的朋友。 2. We have a special offer for our regular patrons. 我们给予老顾客特别的优惠。 3. If needed, give us your special requirements. 如果需要,告诉我们您的特殊要求。 4. This is a special case, deserving special treatment. 这是个特殊的案件，应该获得特殊处理。 5. There are lots of TV Christmas specials for children this year. 今年又很多针对儿童的特别的电视圣诞节目。', '副词: specially 名词: specialness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incense', '[\'ɪnsens]', 'n.香；阿谀 vt.对 ... 敬香；熏香；激怒', '1. Distant dreams rise like incense. 梦在远方化成一缕香。 2. The monk burned a stick of incense in the incense burner. 和尚在香炉里焚上一柱香。 3. To pray for health, every pilgrim would incense and worship here. 想祈求健康去除病魔的信徒们都要到这里烧香拜佛。 4. Some people enjoy using incense. 一些人喜欢使用熏香。', '过去式: incensed 过去分词: incensed 现在分词: incensing 第三人称单数: incenses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circular', '[\'sɜːrkjələr]', 'adj.圆形的；循环的 n.传单；通报', '1. We can compute the circular area with radius. 我们能用半径计算出圆的面积。 2. The full moon has a circular form. 满月呈圆形。 3. Why the wedding ring is circular? 为什么结婚戒指是圆形的? 4. As long as no key is pressed, the scanning goes around in a circular manner. 只要没有按下键，扫描就循环地进行。 5. Have you seen that circular from the new furniture centre? 你见到那家本地新开的家俱总汇的广告了吗？', '副词: circularly 名词: circularity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slacken', '[\'slækən]', 'v.使松弛；使缓慢；变弱', '1. We\'re on the last lap, so don\'t slacken! 我们已处最後阶段，可不要松劲啊！ 2. The bonds of traditional family life began to slacken. 传统的家庭生活的纽带开始松弛。 3. There is no reason to believe that this pace will slacken. 没有理由使人们相信这个速度会变慢。 4. The train slackened speed as we approached the station. 当我们快到车站时，火车减慢了速度。', '过去式: slackened 过去分词: slackened 现在分词: slackening 第三人称单数: slackens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unanimous', '[ju\'nænɪməs]', 'adj.全体一致的；一致同意的', '1. The Chinese are unanimous in their condemnation. 全中国人民一致提出谴责。 2. Politicians from all parties were completely unanimous in condemning his action. 所有党派的政治家们都一致谴责他的行为。 3. He was elected with unanimous approval. 他以全体一致同意而中选。 4. The committee were unanimous that the application should be turned down. 委员会一致同意拒绝这项申请。', '副词: unanimously 名词: unanimousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elation', '[i\'leɪʃn]', 'n.得意洋洋；兴高采烈', '1. He is in a state of pure elation. 他是单纯的得意洋洋。 2. My mother was filled with elation when I got this good job. 我妈妈很高兴我得到这份好工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('warranty', '[\'wɔːrənti]', 'n.保单；根据；保修期', '1. It is foolish to buy a car without a warranty . 购买没有保单的汽车是愚蠢的. 2. Yes, I have a one-year warranty. 是的，我有一年的保修单。 3. What warranty have you for doing this? 你这样做有什么根据? 4. This machine is still under warranty. 这台机器仍在保修期内。', '名词复数: warranties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('loose', '[luːs]', 'adj.松的；宽松的；不确切的；不牢固的；放纵的 n.解放；放任；放纵 v.弄松；释放；放枪 adv.松散地', '1. The screw worked itself loose and the door fell off the cupboard. 螺丝松了，门从橱柜上掉下来了。 2. She wore loose garments in the summer. 她在夏天穿宽松的衣服。 3. Loose labour regulations are one reason. 宽松的劳动规则是原因之一。 4. It is used these days in a very loose sense by a great many people. 现在,许多人用起它来是很不确切的。 5. This will ship to our customer via their consolidator as loose freight. 这将会经由他们的整合者对我们的客户运送如解放船货。 6. Please help me loose the nail, It is rusty and won\'t come out of the wall. 请帮我把这个钉子弄松，它生锈了，拔不出来。', '副词: loosely 比较级: looser 最高级: loosest 名词: looseness 过去式: loosed 过去分词: loosed 现在分词: loosing 第三人称单数: looses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fortitude', '[\'fɔːrtətuːd]', 'n.刚毅；坚毅；不屈不挠', '1. There was no lack of gallantry and fortitude. 并不缺乏勇气和刚毅。 2. I know that my body lacks the fortitude and courage of a strapping young man, and that I cannot find my niche in life. 我知道我身上缺少一个男子汉所应该有的刚毅和果敢，顶不起一片天空。 3. Patience and fortitude conquer all things. 耐心与坚毅征服一切。 4. People who lack internal fortitude often become victims of those who have self-discipline. 那些缺乏内在坚毅的人往往会成为那些自律性很强的人的牺牲品。', '形容词: fortitudinous');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entitled', '[ɪn\'taɪtld]', 'adj.有资格的；已被命名的 动词entitle的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Mr Thant is entitled to a hearing. 如此讲述，吴丹敏是有资格的。 2. She produced a scathing report and said that because the government had said that pensions were protected by law, everybody should get the pension that they were entitled to. 她发布了一份尖锐的报告，声称因为政府有言在先，退休金制度是受法律保护的，因此每个由法律确定其具有资格的人都因该享有。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tardy', '[\'tɑːrdi]', 'adj.迟到的；缓慢的；迟缓的', '1. He was tardy for the meeting. 那次开会他迟到了。 2. The teacher gave the tardy student what for. 老师痛斥了迟到的学生。 3. His boss was dissatisfied with his tardy progress. 老板对他缓慢的进度不满意。 4. She is so forgetful and tardy with work. 她这人就是爱忘事，做什么事情总是拖拖拉拉的。', '副词: tardily 比较级: tardier 最高级: tardiest 名词: tardiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aquarium', '[ə\'kweriəm]', 'n.水族馆；养鱼缸 词根：aqu-（表示水）', '1. The first time I saw seals was in an aquarium. 我第一次看见海豹是在水族馆里。 2. We had such a good time at the aquarium. 我们在水族馆玩得真开心。 3. We bought a gold fish for our aquarium. 我们买了条金鱼放进了家里的鱼缸。 4. He bought an aquarium at the pet store. 他在那家宠物店买了一个养鱼缸。', '名词复数: aquariums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compress', '[\'kɑːmpres]', 'vt.压缩；压榨 n.[医]敷布', '1. Compress this clay into a small ball. 把这块粘土压缩成一个小球。 2. Click the picture that you want to compress. 单击要压缩的图片。', '过去式: compressed 过去分词: compressed 现在分词: compressing 第三人称单数: compresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('procedure', '[prə\'siːdʒər]', 'n.程序；手续；步骤', '1. These procedures are highly irregular. 这些程序是很不合乎规则的。 2. What\'s the procedure for opening a savings account? 开一个储蓄帐户有什么手续? 3. The next procedure is to insert the battery. 接下来的步骤是装进电池。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mundane', '[mʌn\'deɪn]', 'adj.平凡的；世俗的；世界的', '1. I lead a pretty mundane life; nothing interesting ever happens to me. 我生活平凡 2. Even the most mundane things can become objects of beauty in French eyes. 即使是最平凡的事物，在法国人的眼中也是美丽的。 3. The book is full of complicated and sometimes mundane details. 书中充满了复杂,有时甚至是世俗的细节。 4. Each one is contained in a spherical shell surrounded by layers of elemental matter that mark the boundary between mundane space and the unlimited spiritual world. 每个宇宙被物质元素构成的壳所包裹着，这些层层的壳就是物质世界与无限的灵性世界的分界。', '副词: mundanely 名词: mundaneness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('motif', '[moʊ\'tiːf]', 'n.（音乐的）动机；主题；意念；装饰图案', '1. This simple motif runs throughout the entire score. 整个乐章自始至终都贯穿着这样一个简单的主题。 2. Love is an eternal motif in art and literature. 爱情是文学艺术中的永恒主题。 3. The motif of the picture is about peace. 这幅画的主题是和平。 4. This motif is concealed for a month or two. 他这个念头在头两个月还潜而不露。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cooperative', '[koʊ\'ɑːpərətɪv]', 'adj.合作的；协作的 n.合作社', '1. We found him friendly and cooperative. 我们感到他是友好的，乐于合作的。 2. They are trying to adopt a more cooperative posture. 他们正试图采取更为合作的态度。 3. The management would like to thank the staff for being so cooperative. 资方要感谢全体员工的通力合作。 4. The school was very cooperative when we made a film there. 我们到该校拍摄影片时，获得校方的大力协助。 5. They decided to set up a cooperative. 他们决定开办一家合作社。', '副词: cooperatively 名词: cooperativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consistently', '[kən\'sɪstəntlɪ]', 'adv.一致地；始终如一地', '1. The old man lives consistently with the laws of health. 这位老人的生活符合健康原则。 2. The tides come and go consistently with the lunar cycle. 潮汐的来去与月周期一致。 3. We have argued consistently for a change in the law. 我们一直坚持不懈地鼓吹要更改法律。 4. His report consistently begs the whole problem. 他的报告常常回避整个问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abstinence', '[\'æbstɪnəns]', 'n.节制；禁食；戒酒', '1. Satan represents indulgence, instead of abstinence! 撒旦象征放任，而非节制！ 2. Abstinence helps you develop respect for life. 节制帮助你懂得尊重生活。 3. His abstinence from food makes him weak. 禁食使他虚弱。 4. If enteron haemorrhage answers abstinence, delicate fluidity food can eat after haemorrhage stops. 若有消化道出血应禁食，出血停止后可进食清淡流质饮食。', '形容词: abstinent 副词: abstinently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fog', '[fɔːɡ]', 'n.雾；朦胧；迷惑 v.以雾笼罩；使模糊；迷惑', '1. The headlamps penetrated the fog. 车的前灯的光射进雾中。 2. Fog will persist throughout the night. 雾将整夜不散。 3. They used dry ice to fog the stage. 他们用乾冰于舞台变得一片朦胧。 4. A full moon was beginning to rise and peered redly through the upper edges of fog. 一轮满月开始升起，带着红色的光芒在雾气上沿朦胧出现。 5. Steam has fogged the bathroom mirror. 水蒸气把浴室里的镜子遮住了。', '名词: fogger 过去式: fogged 过去分词: fogged 现在分词: fogging 第三人称单数: fogs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ray', '[reɪ]', 'n.光线；射线；辐射 vi.发光；辐射 vt.释放射线；用光线装饰 n.[动]鳐 Ray. n.雷（人名）', '1. My eyes are blind by the direct ray of light. 在光线的直射下，我看不清楚东西。 2. He focused the sun\'s ray on a piece of paper with a burning-glass. 他用一面凸透镜把阳光在纸上聚成焦点。 3. X ray is increasingly used in industry as well. 在工业中X射线也得到了广泛应用。 4. Besides, a global ray-tube tracing method is presented, which is to trace the global wave tubes instead of the many small ray tubes for simulating wave propagations in urban areas. 另外，本论文提出广射线柱追踪法，其中乃是追踪整体射向建筑物表面之辐射电波，有别于一般射线追踪法将发射天线的辐射电波以多个小射线柱来模拟。 5. As time went on,his intelligence rayed out more brightly. 随着时间的推移，他的智慧之光愈加灿烂夺目。 6. The ncident comes just weeks after Crocodile Hunter Steve Irwin died after being stung by a ray. 这场意外发生在鳄鱼捕手史蒂夫艾文被鳐刺死的数星期之后。 7. Ray take a gulp of coffee and rushed out of the room. 雷喝了一大口咖啡，接着便冲出了房间。', '过去式: rayed 过去分词: rayed 现在分词: raying 第三人称单数: rays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fortress', '[\'fɔːrtrəs]', 'n.堡垒；要塞；防御工事', '1. Our soldiers laid siege to the enemy fortress. 我们的战士包围了敌人的堡垒。 2. Complete thawing of the Fortress HUD. 完成了堡垒界面中的融合。 3. They yielded the fortress to the enemy. 他们把要塞让给了敌人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mural', '[\'mjʊrəl]', 'adj.墙壁的；挂在墙壁上的 n.壁画', '1. There is a large mural in the temple. 那个寺院里有一幅很大的壁画。 2. Now we\'re going to learn mural painting. 我们现在要学画壁画儿了。', '名词: muralist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disparage', '[dɪ\'spærɪdʒ]', 'vt.蔑视；贬损', '1. The Arya Samaj did much to encourage Hindu nationalism, but it did not disparage the knowledge of the West, and it established many schools and colleges. 雅利安社大力地鼓励了印度的民族主义，但它并没有蔑视西方的知识，也建立了很多学校和大学。', '副词: disparagingly 名词: disparagement 过去式: disparaged 过去分词: disparaged 现在分词: disparaging 第三人称单数: disparages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('architect', '[\'ɑːrkɪtekt]', 'n.建筑师 n.【喻】缔造者；创造者', '1. He is known as a successful architect. 他以成功的建筑师闻名。 2. The author of the guidebook is an architect by profession. 该旅行指南的作者任职建筑师。 3. The architect was given/presented with a blank cheque to design a new city centre. 设计师被授予全权设计一个新的城市中心区。 4. He was one of the architects of the republic. 他是这个共和国的缔造者之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('option', '[\'ɑːpʃn]', 'n.选择权；可选物 v.得到或获准进行选择', '1. He had no option but to agree. 他除了同意外别无选择。 2. I haven\'t much option in the matter. 在这件事情上我无可选择。 3. Make a list of the various options. 列出可供选择的项目。 4. He had optioned for a film several short stories about two policemen. 他为一部影片选择了几篇关于两位警察的短篇小说。', '过去式: optioned 过去分词: optioned 现在分词: optioning 第三人称单数: options');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revere', '[rɪ\'vɪr]', 'n.（R~）里维尔（美国马萨诸塞州城市避暑胜地）； v.尊敬；敬畏；崇敬', '1. Students revere the old professor. 学生尊敬这位老教授。 2. I revere him greatly. 我很尊敬他。 3. I will teach you to revere and worshipfully fear the Lord. 我要教导你们敬畏耶和华。 4. People came to the memorial to revere the memory of the great leader. 人们来到纪念馆崇敬地纪念这位伟大的领袖。', '过去式: revered 过去分词: revered 现在分词: revering 第三人称单数: reveres');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gaseous', '[\'ɡæsiəs]', 'adj.气体的；气态的；似气体的；无实质的', '1. The lamp is full of gaseous nitrogen. 灯里充满了气体氮。 2. The ball is filled with gaseous mixture. 那个球充满了气体混合物。 3. Steam is water is the gaseous state. 蒸汽是气态的水。 4. Air whether in the gaseous or liquid state is a fluid. 空气，无论是气态的还是液态的，都是一种流体。', '名词: gaseousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corrosive', '[kə\'roʊsɪv]', 'adj.腐蚀的；腐蚀性的；蚀坏的 n.腐蚀物；腐蚀药', '1. It\'s quite important to gain the ability to cope successfully with corrosive atmospheres and particles. 很重要的是获得能够成功地克服气体和粒子腐蚀的能力。 2. To use correctly negative corrodent is to the effective method of preventing metal and its alloy from corroding in the corrosive condition. 正确使用缓蚀剂是防止金属及其合金在腐蚀环境中产生腐蚀的有效方法。 3. With corrosive fluids, the dampener case must also be selected carefully. 由于腐蚀性的液体，减弱器的外壳也须仔细选择。 4. Fasteners should be no corrosive and may consist of self-taping screws, weldable studs, cleats, and clips. 固定的装置不能有腐蚀性的物质，一般自带螺钉，可焊接的螺钉，防滑拴和夹子。', '副词: corrosively 名词: corrosiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anguish', '[\'æŋɡwɪʃ]', 'n.苦闷；痛苦 v.（使）极苦闷；（使）极痛苦', '1. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。 2. I expected something with a terrible anguish that tortured my heart. 在极度揪心的苦闷中我似乎在期待着某种东西。 3. The quarrel caused her great anguish. 争吵给她造成了极大的痛苦。 4. Her mental anguish was beyond words. 她内心的痛苦难以用言语形容。 5. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。', '过去式: anguished 过去分词: anguished 现在分词: anguishing 第三人称单数: anguishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confederacy', '[kən\'fedərəsɪ]', 'n.同盟；联邦；共谋 Confederacy. n.（美国南北战争时期的）南部邦联', '1. This bond of kin represented the real basis of the confederacy. 这种血缘亲属关系是联盟的真实基础。 2. The people of the Creek confederacy occupied some 50 towns. 克里克联邦的人占领了大约50个镇子。 3. They believed the Confederacy would fall if the Union won a big military victory early in the war. 他们相信如果联盟在战争初期就取得大捷胜利的话，南部同盟就会士气低落。', '名词复数: confederacies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('census', '[\'sensəs]', 'n.人口普查；户口普查；统计', '1. The census is taken one time every four years in our country. 我国每四年一次人口普查。 2. The census revealed a declining birth rate. 人口普查结果表明出生率在下降。 3. This census is an invaluable resource for tracing family history. 人口普查是追查家族史的一种宝贵资源。 4. In the United States there is a census every ten years. 在美国每十年做一次户囗调查。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('loyal', '[\'lɔɪəl]', 'adj.忠诚的；忠心的', '1. A loyal man stands by his friends in weal or woe. 一个忠诚的人无论祸福都会支持他的朋友。 2. We are loyal to our motherland. 我们忠于祖国。 3. I may say in all sincerity that you have been my most loyal friend. 我可以非常真诚地说，你一直是我最忠实的朋友。 4. The royal destroyer employs lots of loyal employees. 皇家驱逐舰雇佣了很多忠心的雇员。', '副词: loyally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contrite', '[kən\'traɪt]', 'adj.悔悟了的；后悔的；痛悔的', '1. He was to be contrite and wish to be reconciled. 他必须感到悔悟，并且希望得到赦免。 2. He made a contrite apology. 他深表懊悔地致歉。 3. The look she gave Anna was guilty and contrite. 她给安娜的脸色是内疚和愧悔的。 4. She was contrite the whole morning after her angry outburst. 她发了一通脾气之后整个早上都追悔莫及。', '副词: contritely 名词: contriteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('microscope', '[\'maɪkrəskoʊp]', 'n.显微镜', '1. He focuses the lens of a microscope. 他调整显微镜的透镜以定焦点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frenzy', '[\'frenzi]', 'n.狂乱；狂暴；狂怒', '1. In a frenzy of hate he killed his enemy. 在一阵痛恨的狂乱中，他杀死了敌人。 2. They were singing in a frenzy of joy. 他们欣喜若狂地高声歌唱。 3. His frenzy of the previous day had all calmed down. 他前一天的慌乱都平静下来了。 4. The speaker worked the crowd up into a frenzy. 演讲者煽动起群众疯狂的情绪。', '名词复数: frenzies 过去式: frenzied 过去分词: frenzied 现在分词: frenzying 第三人称单数: frenzies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ransom', '[\'rænsəm]', 'n.赎金；赎身；赎回 vt.赎回', '1. You are our prisoner now and we won\'t release you until a ransom is paid. 你现已遭我们禁锢,要到交出赎金以后,才能放你走。 2. They have to pay a large ransom. 他们不得不付一大笔赎金。 3. They held the travellers for ransom. 他们将旅客当作人质索取赎金。 4. A king\'s ransom would hardly have procured all that my daughters asked for. 即使是一个国王的赎身钱，也买不起我的女儿们所要的东西。 5. They ransomed the kidnapped child with 10,000 dollars. 他们用一万元赎回了被绑架的孩子。', '名词: ransomer 过去式: ransomed 过去分词: ransomed 现在分词: ransoming 第三人称单数: ransoms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intellect', '[\'ɪntəlekt]', 'n.智力；理智；才智非凡的人；知识份子', '1. You estimate his intellect too highly. 你把他的智力评估得太高。 2. The problem challenges us to use our intellect. 这个问题需要我们运用智力。 3. She is short on intellect,but long on shape. 她短于理智而长于姿态。 4. By theory, my behavior is not intellect. 理论上来说，这是不理智的行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shackle', '[\'ʃækl]', 'n.手铐；脚镣；镣铐；束缚物 v.给...戴上镣铐；束缚', '1. The prisoner was fastened by a shackle. 那个犯人被手铐铐着。 2. Shackle were placed on the prisoner\'s hands and feet. 囚犯的手脚都上了镣铐。 3. The prisoner broke the shackle with a hammer and escaped away. 囚犯用锤子打碎镣铐逃跑了。 4. Nowadays, people have shaken off the shackles of some conventions. 今天，人们已经摆脱了一些习俗的束缚。 5. He is too young to shackle himself with the responsibilities of a family. 他还太年轻，不能用家庭责任来束缚自己。', '名词: shackler 过去式: shackled 过去分词: shackled 现在分词: shackling 第三人称单数: shackles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mental', '[\'mentl]', 'adj.思想的；心理的；精神的；脑力的 n.精神病患者', '1. It\'s clear that mental activity does not stop when we\'re asleep. 很显然,我们熟睡的时候,思想活动仍然不会停下来。 2. We should pay more attention to our mental health. 我们应该更注重心理健康。 3. I think such mental disorders are hereditary. 我认为这种精神失调是遗传的。 4. Social life is developed by physical labor and mental labor. 社会生活由于体力劳动和脑力劳动的结合才得以发展。 5. The hospital cares for some fifty mental patients. 这家医院照料五十名左右精神病患者。', '副词: mentally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disprove', '[ˌdɪs\'pruːv]', 'v.证明 ... 是不对的；提出 ... 的反证', '1. In his latest book, he writes that the theory has been disproved. 他在最近写的书里说那种理论已证明不确。 2. The course of a river is almost always disproved of by the source. 河流的方向，几乎常被水源证明是不对的。 3. Their statement incorrect we disprove as follow. 他们的陈述不正确，现提反对意见如下。 4. I defy anyone to disprove the defendant\'s statements. 我倒要看看有没有人能对被告的陈述进行反驳。', '形容词: disprovable 名词: disproval 过去式: disproved 过去分词: disproved 现在分词: disproving 第三人称单数: disproves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('creed', '[kriːd]', 'n.宗教信仰；信念', '1. People of all colors and creeds have come here to celebrate the holiday. 各种肤色和各种宗教信仰的人聚集在这里欢度节日。 2. The laws apply to everyone irrespective of race, creed or colour. 法律适用于所有的人,不分种族、 信仰或肤色。 3. This faith is the abiding creed of our fathers. 这信念是我们祖先的永久的信念。 4. What is your political creed? 你的政治信仰是什么？', '形容词: creedal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('soda', '[\'soʊdə]', 'n.汽水；苏打', '1. He gave me a bottle of orange soda. 他递给我一瓶桔子汽水。 2. They suck soda water through straws. 他们用吸管喝汽水。 3. You can\'t work on soda crackers and sardines. 你光吃苏打饼乾和沙丁鱼不行。 4. Please add some soda to the whisky. 请在威士忌中加些苏打水。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incisive', '[ɪn\'saɪsɪv]', 'adj.一针见血的；敏锐的', '1. He gave a clear and incisive presentation of the matter. 他对整件事作出了一个清楚而又深刻的描述。 2. Many Chinese experts and scholars have an incisive exposition. 中国许多专家学者对此有精辟的论述。 3. He had an incisive and agile mind. 他的思路犀利敏捷。', '副词: incisively 名词: incisiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alkali', '[\'ælkəlaɪ]', 'n.碱', '1. This kind of soil contains much alkali. 这种土壤含碱丰富。 2. The key problem is to overcome alkali in the soil. 关键在于控制土壤里的碱分。 3. Acid and alkali are the basic concept of chemistry. 酸和碱是化学的基本概念。 4. Such detergents do not yellow the wool as alkali tends to do. 这种洗涤剂不会象碱那样使羊毛发黄。', '名词复数: alkalis');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tender', '[\'tendər]', 'adj.温柔的；脆弱的；敏感的；亲切的；嫩的；痛的 v.提出；投标 n.投标；照管人；补给船；煤水车', '1. She is always tender and soft-spoken. 她总是那么温柔,轻声细语。 2. He gave her a tender kiss. 他给了她一个温柔的吻。 3. Love is a river that drowns the tender reed. 爱情是条会淹没柔弱芦苇的河流。 4. Don\'t mention his divorce---it\'s a very tender subject. 别提他离婚的事---那是个敏感话题。 5. I\'ll tender my resignation. 我要提出辞职。 6. His tender for building a mansion has been accepted. 他承办大厦筑的投标被接受了。', '副词: tenderly 比较级: tenderer 最高级: tenderest 名词: tenderness 过去式: tendered 过去分词: tendered 现在分词: tendering 第三人称单数: tenders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('municipal', '[mjuː\'nɪsɪpl]', 'adj.市政的；市的 n.政府证券', '1. An angry mob gathered outside the municipal building. 一群愤怒的暴民聚集在市政大楼的外面。 2. The municipal authorities put forth a new set of traffic regulations some time ago. 前不久市政当局公布了一套新的交通法规。 3. She works in a municipal library. 她在一所市立的图书馆工作。 4. Mr. Charles was elected chairman of the municipal education committee. 查尔斯先生当选为市教育委员会的主任。', '副词: municipally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heredity', '[hə\'redəti]', 'n.遗传；遗传特征', '1. Mendel discovered the laws governing heredity. 门德尔发现了遗传规律。 2. Most of the time it is an issue of heredity. 大部分是因为遗传的原因。 3. Some diseases are present by heredity. 有些疾病是由于遗传导致的。 4. Heredity also plays a role in some types of mental illness. 遗传在某些精神病中也有作用。', '名词复数: heredities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gist', '[dʒɪst]', 'n.要点；主旨', '1. He is quick in grasping the gist of a book. 他敏于了解书的要点。 2. He can not understand the gist of their argument. 他不明白他们争论的要点。 3. I cannot understand the gist of the article. 我不理解这篇文章的主旨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('presumption', '[prɪ\'zʌmpʃn]', 'n.推测；可能性；冒昧；放肆；[法律]推定', '1. I don\'t think that\'s a false presumption. 我认为那并不是错误的推测。 2. On this presumption, she stopped at noon at a neat farm-house, to rest herself. 在这种推测下，到了正午时分，她便在一间整洁的农舍前停下来歇一歇脚。 3. It is not presumption on my part. 在我这方面不算冒昧。 4. Please pardon my presumption in writing to you. 请原谅我很冒昧地写信给你。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('review', '[rɪ\'vjuː]', 'n.复习；回顾；检讨；评审 vt.检阅；评论；温习；检讨 vi.写评论', '1. Before the examination we have a review of the term\'s work. 考试之前，我们复习一学期的功课。 2. A succinct review of this problem with an excellent bibliography has recently appeared. 关于这个问题的一个简明的复习和一份极好的文献目录最近已发表。 3. Perhaps we need a quick review of what we\'ve gone through so far. 或许我们应很快地回顾一下我们前一段时间的工作。 4. Implementation of this phase is under review subject to the finalisation of the statutory plan. 当局现正检讨这期工程的实施，检讨结果视乎拟定法定图则的工作而定。 5. On the square, the commander reviewed the powerful and grandiose guard of honor. 首长在广场上检阅了威武雄壮的仪仗队。 6. Sometimes he reviewed for the principal papers. 他有时为各大报写些评论文章。', '形容词: reviewable 过去式: reviewed 过去分词: reviewed 现在分词: reviewing 第三人称单数: reviews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deficit', '[\'defɪsɪt]', 'n.赤字；逆差；亏损；亏空；不足', '1. The current trade deficit indicates a serious imbalance between our import and export trade. 当前的贸易赤字表明我们的进出口贸易严重失调。 2. That would still leave a substantial trade deficit. 这样仍然会出现巨额贸易逆差。 3. We have a great deficit this year. 我们今年有很大亏损。 4. The company had a deficit of 5000 dollars. 公司亏空了五千美元。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drift', '[drɪft]', 'vi.漂流；漂移；吹积；漂泊；偏离 vt.使漂流；使堆积 n.漂流；趋势；漂泊', '1. The sailors cast the boat off and allowed it to drift away on the tide. 水手解下缆绳，任船随潮流漂走。 2. The boat drifted down the river. 船顺水漂流而下。 3. What causes continents to break up and drift apart? 什么原因导致大陆分裂漂移? 4. Some roads are closed owing to drifting. 有些道路因积雪而封闭。 5. They drift the logs down the river to the sawmills. 他们使那些圆木漂下河流到锯木厂。 6. The general drift of the current was northerly. 这水通常向北流。', '形容词: drifty 过去式: drifted 过去分词: drifted 现在分词: drifting 第三人称单数: drifts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spineless', '[\'spaɪnləs]', 'adj.无脊椎的；没有骨气的；懦弱的', '1. A jellyfish is a spineless animal. 水母是无脊椎动物。 2. My supervisor is a spineless person. He never stands behind his decisions. 我的主管是一个没骨气的人。他不敢为他做的决定负责。 3. At a time of crisis, why are Britain\'s politicians so spineless? 危急时刻，为何英国政治家如此懦弱？', '副词: spinelessly 名词: spinelessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('urban', '[\'ɜːrbən]', 'adj.城市的；都市的', '1. In some developing countries more and more people are migrating to urban areas. 在某些发展中的国家,越来越多的人向市区迁移。 2. The quality of urban living has been damaged by excessive noise levels. 城市生活的质量已被过度的噪音所破坏。 3. You can find out many advantages in urban life. 你会发现都市生活中有许多便利之处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discard', '[dɪs\'kɑːrd]', 'vt.丢弃；抛弃 vi.丢牌 n.丢牌；废牌', '1. He discarded his winter clothing. 他把冬天穿的衣服都丢弃了。 2. My mother-in-law would discard them on the spot. 我的岳母是会当场把它们扔掉的。 3. History discarded him. 他被历史所抛弃。 4. You\'ve got to discard before you can pick up another card. 你得先打出一张牌，才能拿另一张牌。', '形容词: discardable 名词: discarder 过去式: discarded 过去分词: discarded 现在分词: discarding 第三人称单数: discards');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('culmination', '[ˌkʌlmɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.顶点；最高潮', '1. The show marked the culmination of months of hard work. 这场演出标志着几个月艰辛工作的最终成果。 2. The space race reached its culmination in the first moon walk. 太空竞争以第一次在月球行走而达到顶峰。 3. It may truly be regarded as the culmination of classical Greek geometry. 这确实可以看成是古典希腊几何的登峰造级之作。 4. The culmination of love is blindness. 爱情的最高潮就是愚昧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decipher', '[dɪ\'saɪfər]', 'vt.译解；辨认', '1. He could decipher military signals. 他能破译军事信号。 2. We can decipher the password intercepted by broadcasting station. 我们能破译电台截获的密码。 3. Can you decipher her scrawl? 你能辩认出她乱写的是什么吗? 4. I can\'t decipher what is inscribed on the pillar. 我认不出刻在柱子上的是什么。', '形容词: decipherable 名词: decipherer 过去式: deciphered 过去分词: deciphered 现在分词: deciphering 第三人称单数: deciphers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stodgy', '[\'stɑːdʒi]', 'adj.笨重的；沉闷的；式样难看的；难消化的', '1. They are stodgy, slow-moving players who are asleep at the helm. 这些都是体型笨重、行动迟缓的对手，他们还在睡梦中呢。 2. It\'s not stodgy to talk about money. 谈论金钱并不庸俗。 3. She poked fun at Alec because he was shy and stodgy. 她开亚历克的玩笑，因为他羞怯，同时还有些枯燥沉闷。 4. These were not the old stodgy ads listing goods for sale. 这不是那种列明打折商品的旧式、乏味的广告。', '副词: stodgily 比较级: stodgier 最高级: stodgiest 名词: stodginess');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('err', '[er]', 'v.犯错；做错', '1. Instead, the policy maker may decide to err on the side of safety. 相反，为了公众安全决策者会作出决策，而不惜犯错。 2. They know to err oneself, alarmed, you see me, I see you, how is knowing good. 他们自知犯错，一阵惊慌，你看我，我看你，不知如何是好。 3. She would not err in any way, if she could help it. 只要有可能的话，她要避免做错任何动作。', '过去式: erred 过去分词: erred 现在分词: erring 第三人称单数: errs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('claim', '[kleɪm]', 'n.要求；要求权；主张；断言；声称；要求物 vt.要求；请求；主张；声称；断言', '1. The matter claimed our serious attention. 这件事需要我们认真注意。 2. Did you claim on the insurance after your car accident? 出了车祸后，你向保险公司要求赔偿了吗？ 3. The government would not even consider his claim for money. 政府甚至不考虑他的赔款要求。 4. He set up a claim to the throne. 他自称王位是属于他的。', '形容词: claimable 名词: claimer 过去式: claimed 过去分词: claimed 现在分词: claiming 第三人称单数: claims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conjure', '[\'kʌndʒə]', 'v.变戏法；恳求；唤起；以咒文召唤', '1. Jean can conjure up a good meal in half an hour. 琼能在半小时内变戏法似的做出一顿美味的饭菜。 2. Be on your guard, I conjure you. 千万要警惕呀，我恳求你。', '过去式: conjured 过去分词: conjured 现在分词: conjuring 第三人称单数: conjures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lubricant', '[\'luːbrɪkənt]', 'n.润滑剂', '1. Sweat is the lubricant of success. 汗水是成功的润滑剂。 2. Drain lubricant to the correct level. 将润滑剂排放到正确的高度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('haven', '[\'heɪvn]', 'n.港口；避难所 v.安置 ... 于港中；庇护', '1. A dear ship stands long in the haven. 一只贵重的船在港口停留很久。 2. Terrorists will not find a safe haven here. 恐怖分子在这里将找不到安身之处。 3. His own room seemed a safe and comfortable haven. 他自己的房间看来是一个安全而惬意的避难所。 4. They have made their home a haven for the homeless orphans. 他们把自己的家变成了无家可归的孤儿们的避难所。 5. He havened his motorboat on a small harbour. 他把摩托艇停泊在一个小港上。', '过去式: havened 过去分词: havened 现在分词: havening 第三人称单数: havens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('curt', '[kɜːrt]', 'adj.(言语)简短失礼的；简短的； 草率的', '1. He rapped out a series of curt commands. 他大声发出了一连串简短的命令。 2. `No!\' was his curt rejoinder. 他草率地回答了一声｀不!＇ 3. He rapped out a series of curt commands. 他大声发出了一连串简短的命令。', '副词: curtly 比较级: curter 最高级: curtest 名词: curtness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apathetic', '[ˌæpə\'θetɪk]', 'adj.缺乏感情的；缺乏兴趣的；无动于衷的；冷淡的', '1. He hustled on his overcoat, and bustled about in a way that showed that an energetic fit had superseded the apathetic one. 他披上大衣，那种匆忙的样子说明他跃跃欲试的心情已压倒了无动于衷的心情。', '副词: apathetically 异体字: apathetical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vary', '[\'veri]', 'v.改变；变化；使多样化', '1. Although this is the general approach, you can vary it to some degree. 尽管这是常规方法,但可以在一定程度上改变它。 2. The prices of some goods vary with the season. 某些货物的价格随着季节的变化而变动。 3. Teachers shall vary their lessons to make them more interesting. 为了增加趣味，教师应该使自己的课多样化。', '副词: varyingly 过去式: varied 过去分词: varied 现在分词: varying 第三人称单数: varies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compound', '[\'kɑːmpaʊnd]', 'n.化合物；复合词；复合物 n.院子(用围墙圈起来的场地） adj.化合的；【语】（词语等）复合的；【植】复合的；【动】群体的 vt.混合；调合；使严重；私了；【经】以复利计算 vi.妥协', '1. Water is a compound of hydrogen and oxygen. 水是氢和氧的化合物。 2. \'Bus conductor\', \'dark-haired\' and \'policeman\' are compounds. bus conductor,dark-haired和policeman都是复合词。 3. Medicines are usually compounds. 药品通常是复合物。 4. All prisoners were frog-marched (out) into the compound. 犯人都被迫反剪双臂(出来)进入院子。 5. \"Fingerprint\" is a compound word. “Fingerprint”（指纹）是一个复合词。 6. He compounded various ingredients into an effective drug. 他将各种成分混合成一种有效的药物。 7. He compounded with his creditors for a remission of what he owed. 他和他的债权人谈妥免除其债务。', '形容词: compoundable 名词: compounder 过去式: compounded 过去分词: compounded 现在分词: compounding 第三人称单数: compounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solicitous', '[sə\'lɪsɪtəs]', 'adj.热切的；焦虑的；挂念的；关心的', '1. I am solicitous of his help. 我渴得到他的帮助。 2. He was very solicitous for her safe return. 他心神不定 3. She was very solicitous for our welfare. 她非常挂念我们的福利问题。 4. We are all solicitous about his health. 我们都为他的身体担心。', '副词: solicitously 名词: solicitousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meteorite', '[\'miːtiəraɪt]', 'n.陨石；流星', '1. He discovered an unusual meteorite. 他发现了一块奇异的陨石。 2. There\'s a meteorite that hit the ground near here. 附近有颗流星刚掉下来', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boulder', '[\'boʊldər]', 'n.大圆石；巨砾', '1. He was unable to budge the boulder. 他搬不动那块大圆石。 2. We hear the sound of the river rush past boulder below. 我们听到河水奔腾而过大圆石的声音。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reluctant', '[rɪ\'lʌktənt]', 'adj.不情愿的；勉强的', '1. They were very reluctant to help. 他们不大愿意帮忙。 2. I was reluctant to do over the stitching in the dress. 我不愿意把衣服上的线脚拆了重缝。 3. By 1982 they had become reluctant to extend new loans to public borrowers. 到1982年，他们已不愿向公共借贷者发放新的贷款。 4. Margaret gave him a reluctant consent. 玛格丽特勉强答应了他。', '副词: reluctantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('propose', '[prə\'poʊz]', 'v.打算；计划；向 ... 提议；求婚；提名', '1. I propose an early start tomorrow morning. 我打算明天早上早点出发。 2. He proposed to buy and run a farm. 他计划购买并经营一个农场。 3. The committee proposed that new legislation should be drafted. 委员会建议着手起草新法规。 4. He had proposed marriage, unsuccessfully, twice already. 他已经两次求婚，均未成功。', '名词: proposer 过去式: proposed 过去分词: proposed 现在分词: proposing 第三人称单数: proposes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('restrict', '[rɪ\'strɪkt]', 'vt.限制；约束', '1. In a move to restrict imports, the government raised custom duties. 政府在限制进口的措施中提高了关税。 2. Recent laws have tended to restrict the freedom of the press. 新法例有限制新闻自由的趋势。 3. I restrict myself to smoking two cigarettes a day. 我限定自己每天只抽两支烟。 4. Fog restricted visibility. 雾天能见度很低。', '名词: restrictor 过去式: restricted 过去分词: restricted 现在分词: restricting 第三人称单数: restricts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bland', '[blænd]', 'adj.温和的；不油腻的；引不起兴趣的；平淡无奇的', '1. He said this with his face expanding in a bland smile. 他这样说着，脸上绽开了温和的笑容。 2. The sight of that bland,impregnably righteous face has been enough to make their blood run cold. 看见那张温和的而又非常正直的脸足够使他们冷静下来。 3. As a result news coverage tends to be bland. 结果新闻报道往往是平淡无奇的。 4. This will tend to produce either bland, have-a-nice-day standardisation of, more usually, various idiolects-private versions of the language---that work only in specific contexts. 这也许会带来平淡无奇的标准化语言，但更多的则是适用于特定环境的充满个人色彩的语汇。', '副词: blandly 比较级: blander 最高级: blandest 名词: blandness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impassive', '[ɪm\'pæsɪv]', 'adj.无感情的；无表情的；冷漠的；平静的', '1. He listened with an impassive face. 他面无表情地听着。 2. He was content to stand by as an impassive spectator. 他满足于站在旁边做一个冷漠的旁观者。 3. He still wore the same impassive and preoccupied air. 他仍旧有那种心情缭乱而力自镇静的神气。', '副词: impassively 名词: impassiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('naive', '[naɪ\'iːv]', 'adj.天真的；幼稚的', '1. He derides her naive attitude. 他嘲弄她天真的态度。 2. Children always ask naive questions. 小孩子总问天真的问题。 3. This theory was intended to deceive naive people. 这一理论旨在欺骗天真群众。 4. The politician made a naive decision. 这个政治家做了一个幼稚的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maim', '[meɪm]', 'v.使伤残', '1. He was maimed in a First World War battle. 他在第一次世界大战的一埸战斗中受伤致残。 2. She survived the accident but she was maimed for life and will never walk again. 她在意外事故中大难不死，但却终身残废，再也不能行走了。', '名词: maimer 过去式: maimed 过去分词: maimed 现在分词: maiming 第三人称单数: maims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pose', '[poʊz]', 'v.摆姿势；把...摆正位置；造成；提出；假装 n.姿态；姿势；装腔作势', '1. Please sit still while you pose for your photo. 你摆好姿势拍照时请坐着别动。 2. The artist posed his model carefully. 这个艺术家仔细地把他的模型放好。 3. All the subjects are well posed. 所有的东西都摆好了位置。 4. Pollution poses a threat to the continued existence of this species. 污染对这一物种的继续生存造成了威胁。 5. She always liked to strike a noble pose. 她总是喜欢摆出一副高贵的样子。', '形容词: posable 过去式: posed 过去分词: posed 现在分词: posing 第三人称单数: poses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rainbow', '[\'reɪnboʊ]', 'n.彩虹；五彩缤纷的排列；幻想', '1. Do you see rainbow? 你看到彩虹了吗？ 2. A rainbow is usually seen after a heavy rain. 大雨之后常有彩虹。 3. Now we can bask in the rainbow of the memories that we\'ll nurture in the years ahead. 在未来岁月里，让我们在记忆的长虹里永远珍藏对他的怀念。 4. We saw a beautiful rainbow across the sky. 我们看到了一条五彩缤纷的虹横贯天空。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anchor', '[\'æŋkər]', 'n.锚；锚状物；依靠；新闻节目主播；压阵队员 v.抛锚；停泊；用锚系住；担任（广播电视新闻节目）的主持人', '1. The ship dragged its anchor during the night. 夜里,船把锚拖动了。 2. Hope is his only anchor. 希望是他唯一的依靠。 3. He was then doing the anchor. 他当时正主持新闻广播节目。 4. The anchor man in a relay team runs last. 接力队中的主力跑最后一棒。 5. The ship was anchored off the shore. 船在海岸处抛了锚。', '过去式: anchored 过去分词: anchored 现在分词: anchoring 第三人称单数: anchors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disaster', '[dɪ\'zæstər]', 'n.灾难', '1. They had led the country into economic disaster. 他们把国家带入了经济灾难中。 2. The disaster caused him to waver in his faith. 这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。 3. He spoke darkly of possible future disaster. 他悲观地说将来可能大难临头。 4. We are all pervaded with a sense of disaster. 我们普遍有大祸降临的感觉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('venerate', '[\'venəreɪt]', 'v.尊敬；尊崇；崇拜', '1. They came to venerate him as a symbolic figure. 他们把他当作偶像来崇拜。 2. They venerate the old man\'s memory. 他们怀着崇敬之情纪念那位老人。 3. And love, young man, love and venerate the ideal. 青年人啊，热爱理想，崇敬理想吧。 4. Merchant should aways venerate his heart. 商人应该尊崇自己的内心.', '名词: venerator 过去式: venerated 过去分词: venerated 现在分词: venerating 第三人称单数: venerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ken', '[ken]', 'n.视野；眼界；知识范围 v.知道；了解 Ken. n.肯恩(男子名)', '1. His ideas are quite beyond my ken. 我很不理解他的想法。 2. I can\'t repair a car engine; it\'s quite beyond my ken. 我不会修理汽车引擎，这超出了我的知识范围。', '过去式: kenned/kent 过去分词: kenned/kent 现在分词: kenning 第三人称单数: kens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('destination', '[ˌdestɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.目的地；终点', '1. We eventually arrived at our destination. 我们终于到达了目的地。 2. The parcel was sent to the wrong destination. 包裹送错了地方。 3. The coach followed a rather devious course to its destination. 长途汽车要绕很多弯路才到达目的地。 4. The destination of bus No. 8 is the State University. 8路车的终点是州立大学。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hydrogen', '[\'haɪdrədʒən]', 'n.氢', '1. Hydrogen is highly explosive. 氢极易爆炸。 2. Hydrogen and oxygen are gases. 氢和氧是气体。 3. A molecule of water consists of two atoms of hydrogen and one atom of oxygen. 水分子含有两个氢原子和一个氧原子。', '形容词: hydrogenous 简写符号: H');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adage', '[\'ædɪdʒ]', 'n.格言；谚语；古话', '1. The adage really enlightened me since my youth. 这句格言从我青年时代起就给了我真正的启示。 2. Nearly 150 years later, variations of this adage are still quoted. 差不多在150年之后，这个变化了的谚语一直被引用。 3. But the old adage that men grow into office has not proved true in my experience. 但是，根据我的经验，人们所谓的工作岗位造就人材这句古话并不正确。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spare', '[sper]', 'adj.备用的；多余的；闲置的 v.抽出；饶恕；赦免；节约 n.备用品；剩余', '1. Do you have a spare tire? 你有备用轮胎吗? 2. Please stay with us. We have a spare room for you. 请住下吧,我们有给你的备用房间。 3. What do you like doing in your spare time? 你在闲暇时喜欢做什么？ 4. Can you bear me a hand tomorrow?I want to rearrange some things in our spare room. 明天你能帮个忙吗?我想把我家闲置着的那个房间里的一些东西新整理安排一下。 5. Can you spare me five minutes? 你能抽出五分钟和我谈谈吗？ 6. I\'ve lost my key and I haven\'t got a spare. 我把钥匙丢了，还没有备用的。', '副词: sparely 比较级: sparer 最高级: sparest 名词: spareness 过去式: spared 过去分词: spared 现在分词: sparing 第三人称单数: spares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transfer', '[træns\'fɜːr]', 'v.转移；调任；转乘 n.迁移；移动；换车；汇兑', '1. The exhibition was transferred to another city two days later. 两天后,这个展会转移到另外一个城市。 2. She has been transferred to another department. 她已被调往另一个部门。 3. I took the subway and then transferred to the bus. 我搭乘地铁然后再改乘公共汽车。 4. Our company will have a transfer to London. 我们公司将迁往伦敦。', '形容词: transferable 名词: transferability 过去式: transferred 过去分词: transferred 现在分词: transferring 第三人称单数: transfers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scatter', '[\'skætər]', 'vt.散播；撒；驱散 vi.分散；消散 n.散布；零星少量', '1. She wanted us to scatter her ashes to the winds. 她希望我们把她的骨灰散播到风中。 2. The farmers were scattering seed on the fields. 农夫把种子撒在田里。 3. Let\'s try not to scatter food or drink on the table. 别把饭或汤撒到桌上。 4. The police scattered the crowd. 警察驱散了人群。 5. Small villages scatter at the foot of the mountain. 村庄零零落落地散布在山脚下。 6. She gave the soup a quick scatter of herbs. 她把香料快速撒在汤上。', '名词: scatterer 过去式: scattered 过去分词: scattered 现在分词: scattering 第三人称单数: scatters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('becoming', '[bɪ\'kʌmɪŋ]', 'adj.合适的；适当的；好看的 动词become的现在分词.', '1. Blue always looks very becoming on her. 她穿蓝色的服装总是很合适的。 2. A becoming dress lends charm to a lady. 合身的服装会给女士增添魅力。 3. The dress is very becoming on you. 这条衣服穿在你身上真好看。', '副词: becomingly 名词: becomingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arduous', '[\'ɑːrdʒuəs]', 'adj.费力的；辛勤的；险峻的', '1. They walk from their villages and make the arduous ascent of Taishan. 困难的，险峻的，费力的，刻苦的。 2. It is arduous, it is difficult, but once you can do it, you will have become a different person, a different being in a different world. 它是费力的，它是困难的，但是你一旦做到，你会变成一个不同的人，一个不同的存有者，在一个不同的世界里。 3. The 1 million farmers here ever were this blackland ground to win completely homebred grain with arduous sweat the reputation of the biggest county. 这里的百万农民曾用辛勤的汗水为这块黑土地赢得全国产粮第一大县的声名。 4. They walk from their villages and make the arduous ascent of Taishan. 困难的，险峻的，费力的，刻苦的。', '副词: arduously 名词: arduousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conciliatory', '[kən\'sɪliətɔːri]', 'adj.调和的；安抚的', '1. Her expression was not conciliatory. 她的脸色显得毫不调和。 2. His letter was couched in conciliatory terms. 他那封信里使用了表示和解的言辞。 3. A more conciliatory approach is more productive. 更加柔和的手段总是更有成效。 4. The politician struck a conciliatory tone with his former adversaries. 那个政客用安抚的口吻跟以前的对手说话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sole', '[soʊl]', 'adj.独占的；唯一的 n.脚底；鞋底 n.鳎鱼 vt.给(鞋)换底', '1. He has the sole agency for Ford car. 他有福特汽车的独家代理权。 2. His sole motive is to make more money. 他唯一的动机就是多赚钱。 3. Farming is his sole livelihood. 他唯一的谋生之道就是务农。 4. He has pain on the sole of his feet. 他脚底很痛。 5. I\'m having my shoes soled and heeled. 我要叫人给鞋子换鞋底和鞋跟。', '名词复数: sole 过去式: soled 过去分词: soled 现在分词: soling 第三人称单数: soles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('freight', '[freɪt]', 'n.（货运）运费；货运；货物 vt.装货于；运送', '1. At an auction, the buyer pays the freight. 在拍卖会上，买家支付运费。 2. The freight must be added to the cost of the goods. 运费必须打入货的成本。 3. We can send it by air/sea freight. 我们可以空运[海运]。 4. Eight thousand tons of freight were being landed each day. 每天卸货8000吨上岸。 5. They freighted the boat with bananas. 他们把香蕉装上船。', '过去式: freighted 过去分词: freighted 现在分词: freighting 第三人称单数: freights');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('erroneous', '[ɪ\'roʊniəs]', 'adj.错误的；不正确的', '1. We must oppose these erroneous trends of thought. 我们必须反对所有这些错误的思潮。 2. Sometimes this information may be erroneous. 有时候这种信息是错误的。 3. Some of the erroneous pictures of America are painted by others. 但是对美国的一些不正确的描述也来自外部世界。 4. So on bad CD-ROM drives it is possible that you receive erroneous results. 以至于使用不好的光驱抓轨，可能会接收到不正确的结果。', '副词: erroneously 名词: erroneousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clandestine', '[klæn\'destɪn]', 'adj.秘密的(常指违法的行为)', '1. They had a clandestine meeting in the park yesterday. 昨天他们在公园开了个黑会。', '副词: clandestinely 名词: clandestineness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deference', '[\'defərəns]', 'n.顺从；敬重', '1. His immediate deference made her regretful. 他毫不迟疑的顺从使她感到有些抱歉。 2. I changed my plan in deference to your opinion. 我听从你的意见，改变了计划。 3. They are married in church out of deference to their parents\' wish. 他们遵从父母的愿望在教堂举行了婚礼。 4. We all showed deference to his skill. 我们都敬重他的熟练技巧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scurry', '[\'skɜːri]', 'v.小步疾走；急赶 n.快跑声；疾走', '1. They scurried in out of the cold. 他们冻得很快跑进来了。 2. The rain sent everyone scurrying for shelter. 这阵雨把大家浇得纷纷找地方躲避。 3. I heard a scurry of footsteps. 我听到一阵匆忙奔跑的脚步声。 4. There was a great scurry for bargains. 大家急忙着去抢购特价品。', '名词复数: scurries 过去式: scurried 过去分词: scurried 现在分词: scurrying 第三人称单数: scurries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('puddle', '[\'pʌdl]', 'n.水坑；地上积水；胶泥 v.搅浊；在泥污中打滚；排尿', '1. The puddle evaporated rapidly in the sun. 水坑在阳光下迅速蒸发。 2. I have rarely seen such a huge puddle of milk. 我几乎没看过这么大的奶水坑。', '形容词: puddly 过去式: puddled 过去分词: puddled 现在分词: puddling 第三人称单数: puddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equivocate', '[ɪ\'kwɪvəkeɪt]', 'vi.说模棱两可的话；支吾其词', '1. Don\'t equivocate with me I want a straight answer to a straight question! 别跟我绕弯子--我问的问题直截了当，回答也要直截了当！', '名词: equivocator 过去式: equivocated 过去分词: equivocated 现在分词: equivocating 第三人称单数: equivocates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('soluble', '[\'sɑːljəbl]', 'adj.可溶解的；可解决的', '1. Soluble metallic hydroxides are bases that are alkalies. 可溶解的金属氢氧化合物都是碱。 2. A subsequent wet depithing serves to remove soluble and strongly adhering pith. 后续的除髓工序可以继续除去可溶解的和粘附牢固的蔗髓。', '副词: solubly 名词: solubleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('linen', '[\'lɪnɪn]', 'n.亚麻布；亚麻线；亚麻制品 adj.亚麻布制的；亚麻的', '1. The old linen smelled of the tomb. 旧亚麻布散发出墓地的气味。 2. Flax is used to make linen. 亚麻用来织亚麻布。 3. Low elasticity, imparting a hard, smooth texture, makes linen subject to wrinkling. 弹性较低，使得质地坚硬光滑，亚麻制品容易起皱纹。 4. He has abandoned suits in favour of linen jackets and khaki trousers and no tie. 他不穿西装，喜欢穿亚麻夹克和卡其布长裤，而且不打领带。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impressive', '[ɪm\'presɪv]', 'adj.给人深刻印象的', '1. His collection of paintings is the most impressive. 他的绘画收藏令人叹为观止。 2. The report looks impressive but it\'s really nothing but waffle. 这篇报告貌似冠冕堂皇，实际上空洞无物。 3. Among his many good qualities, punctuality is the most impressive one. 在他众多优秀品质中,守时给人留下了最深刻印象。 4. Their success is all the more impressive when you consider the efforts they\'ve made. 如果你考虑到他们所付出的努力,你就会觉得他们的成功真的很了不起。', '副词: impressively 名词: impressiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glacier', '[\'ɡleɪʃər]', 'n.冰河；冰川', '1. The glacier dislocated the great stones. 冰河搬动了巨石。 2. The gorge was formed by a glacier. 这个峡谷是由冰河形成的。 3. The upper surface of glacier is riven by crevasses. 冰川的上表面已裂成冰隙。 4. He showed me a drawing of the glacier. 他给我看一张冰川图。', '形容词: glaciered');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stack', '[stæk]', 'n.堆；一大堆；【计】存储栈；迭式存储器，栈式存储器；存储栈数据 v.堆积；堆放', '1. The grain has gone mouldy in the stack. 垛里的谷子发霉了。 2. He placed his books in a neat stack. 他把书整整齐齐放成一堆。 3. I\'ve got stacks of work to do. 我有一大堆活儿要做。 4. There is a stack of dishes to be washed in the kitchen. 厨房里还有一大堆盘子要洗。 5. Please stack the materials up here. 请把材料堆在这里。', '形容词: stackable 名词: stacker 过去式: stacked 过去分词: stacked 现在分词: stacking 第三人称单数: stacks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excessive', '[ɪk\'sesɪv]', 'adj.过分的；过多的', '1. Excessive patriotism can lead to xenophobia. 爱国主义过了头即可导致仇视一切外国人。 2. Excessive dosage of this drug can result in injury to the liver. 这种药使用过量会损害肝脏。 3. The quality of urban living has been damaged by excessive noise levels. 城市生活的质量已被过度的噪音所破坏。 4. I consider the excessive smoking and drinking tend to cloud the brain. 我认为过多的抽烟和过量的酗酒，会使人的头脑迟钝。', '副词: excessively 名词: excessiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('breach', '[briːtʃ]', 'n.破坏；违背；决裂；裂口；（浪的）冲击 v.违反；突破；在 ... 上打开缺口', '1. Union officials denounced the action as a breach of the agreement. 工会负责人谴责这一行动破坏了协议。 2. You are in breach of your contract. 你违反了你签的合同。 3. It caused a lifelong breach with his father. 这使得他们父子终身失和。 4. The huge waves made a breach in the sea wall. 大浪在堤上冲出一个缺口。 5. He never do the things breach the benefits of group. 他不做任何违背集体利益的事。', '过去式: breached 过去分词: breached 现在分词: breaching 第三人称单数: breaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('negate', '[nɪ\'ɡeɪt]', 'vt.否定；否认；使无效', '1. How can you negate God? 你怎么能否定上帝的存在? 2. These facts negate your theory. 这些事实否定了你的理论。 3. This power is always conceived in relation to men; it is not the power to do but the power to attract. It is a power that negates itself. (cf. Beauty, Susan Sontag) 这种力量也常常被认为和男性有关；这不是一种行动力而是一种吸引力。这是一种否定自身的力量。 4. The story negated the trade supported by the government. 该项报道否认了此项贸易受到政府的支持。', '名词: negator 过去式: negated 过去分词: negated 现在分词: negating 第三人称单数: negates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delicate', '[\'delɪkət]', 'adj.微妙的；精美的；纤细的；脆弱的；敏锐的；美味的', '1. The international situation is very delicate at present. 目前的国际形势极其微妙。 2. He persecuted me with various delicate questions. 他用种种微妙的问题把我难倒了。 3. She wears a dress with delicate lace. 她穿了一件带有精致花边的裙子。 4. Don\'t grasp at the delicate branch, or you may break it. 不要去抓这嫩枝,你会把它折断的。', '副词: delicately 名词: delicateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brittle', '[\'brɪtl]', 'adj.易碎的；尖利的；脆弱的 n.果仁薄脆糖', '1. The ice is brittle as the thin glass. 这些冰像薄的玻璃一样易碎。 2. The pond was covered in a brittle layer of ice. 池塘覆盖了一层易碎的冰。 3. Constant stress has made our nerves brittle. 我们长期处于紧张状态，神经已经吃不消了。 4. The orchestra was brittle in tone. 管弦乐队演奏的曲调尖利刺耳。', '副词: brittlely 比较级: brittler 最高级: brittlest 名词: brittleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('artifact', '[\'ɑrtəˌfækt]', 'n.人工制品；典型产物；【医】非源自脑中的电波，伪差，假象，人为现象', '1. In the wrong hands this powerful artifact has the ability to unravel the soul. 在错误手这强有力的人工制品有能力解开灵魂。 2. A user interface is an artifact, not directly associated with the goals of a user. 用户界面是人造的，并非直接和用户的目标相关。 3. Working code is the single most important artifact. 工作代码是一个最重要的工件。', '形容词: artifactual');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coupon', '[\'kuːpɑːn]', 'n.息票；参赛表；票券；礼券；(购物)优惠券', '1. This coupon can be redeemed at any of our branches. 这种息票可在我们的任何分行兑现。 2. let\'s fill in a football coupon. 我们填一下足球彩票吧。 3. Coupon must be presented when ordering. 请于落单前出示此券。 4. Please remember to bring the meal coupon. 会议代表凭餐票用餐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dim', '[dɪm]', 'adj.暗淡的；模糊的；笨的 v.使暗淡；使失去光泽 n.车头近光灯；停车灯', '1. Most comets are so dim that they can not be seen by the naked eye. 彗星很暗淡,肉眼看不见。 2. He spoke with firmness, but his face was very sad and his eyes at times were dim. 他讲话时预期坚定，但面带愁容，时而眼神暗淡。 3. I made out two dim shapes in the gloom. 我在朦胧中看出有两个模糊的影子。 4. She is rather dim about the importance of keeping records. 她不明白作记录的重要性。 5. Old age hasn\'t dimmed her memory. 她虽然年事已高，但记忆并未模糊。', '副词: dimly 比较级: dimmer 最高级: dimmest 名词: dimness 过去式: dimmed 过去分词: dimmed 现在分词: dimming 第三人称单数: dims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hurl', '[hɜːrl]', 'v.用力投掷；愤慨地说出；丢下', '1. The hunter hurled his spear at the tiger. 猎人用力把他的长矛向虎投去。 2. I\'ll hurl him out of the club if he dare tell the secret! 如果他胆敢泄密，我就要把他赶出俱乐部。 3. To hurl abuse is in no way to fight. 谩骂决不是战斗。 4. Businessmen will hurl their money about to get noticed. 商人愿意挥霍钱财来引起注意。', '名词: hurler 过去式: hurled 过去分词: hurled 现在分词: hurling 第三人称单数: hurls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wax', '[wæks]', 'n.蜡；蜂蜡 vt.(用蜡)涂 vi.变圆', '1. Blobs of wax covered the candlestick. 烛台上全是一团团的蜡。 2. He is modeling a unicorn in wax . 他在用蜡制作独角兽。 3. They bought wax and honey up by the great. 他们大量购进蜜蜡和蜂蜜。 4. Why did she have to wax the floors herself? 她干什么非要自己动手给地板打腊? 5. The moon is waxing. 月亮越来越圆。', '过去式: waxed 过去分词: waxed 现在分词: waxing 第三人称单数: waxes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wreck', '[rek]', 'v.使…失事；使…遇难；破坏 n.遇难；残骸；破坏；（船）失事下沉', '1. The ship was wrecked on the rock. 船在岩石上撞毁了。 2. The train wrecked at midnight. 这列火车半夜出轨了。 3. His drinking wrecked their marriage. 他的酗酒毁坏了他们的婚姻。 4. Nobody can wreck the friendship between us. 没有人能破坏我们之间的友谊。 5. They save the cargo from the wreck. 他们从遇难船上抢救出货物。', '过去式: wrecked 过去分词: wrecked 现在分词: wrecking 第三人称单数: wrecks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('destruction', '[dɪ\'strʌkʃn]', 'n.破坏；毁灭', '1. It will cause pollution and the destruction of our seas and oceans. 这会引起污染，破坏我们的海洋和江河。 2. Scientific knowledge was perverted to help cause destruction and war. 科学知识被滥用于破坏和战争。 3. Gambling was his destruction. 赌博把他毁了。 4. We must not bring mass destruction on ourselves by waging an atomic world war. 我们千万不要发动世界核子战争而自招集体毁灭。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irrevocable', '[ɪ\'revəkəbl]', 'adj.不能挽回的；不能取消的；不能变更的', '1. The doom which I have passed upon her is irrevocable. 我对她下的判决是不能挽回的。 2. We ask you to use an irrevocable letter of credit. 我们要求您们开一张不可撤销的信用状。 3. The decision has been made and is irrevocable. 木已成舟已作出决定，无法反悔 4. His life was set on an irrevocable course. 他的生活道路不可改变。', '副词: irrevocably 名词: irrevocability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confession', '[kən\'feʃən]', 'n.自认；自白；招供；忏悔', '1. They saw compromise as a confession of weakness. 他们认为妥协就是自认孱弱。 2. Such an explanation is tantamount to a confession. 这样一种解释等于一篇自白。 3. His confession involved a number of other politicians in the affair. 他的自白供出其他一些政治人物也涉及此事。 4. By clever questioning they trapped him into making a confession. 他们用巧妙的提问诱使他招认了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intoxicate', '[ɪn\'tɒksɪkeɪt]', 'vt. 下毒； 使 ... 陶醉', '1. Cherishing a rose means to intoxicate yourself on her beauty more than pull her throns out. 喜欢玫瑰意思是要我们陶醉它的美丽，而不是去除它的刺。', '形容词: intoxicative 副词: intoxicatingly 名词: intoxication 过去式: intoxicated 过去分词: intoxicated 现在分词: intoxicating 第三人称单数: intoxicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plead', '[pliːd]', 'v.辩护；恳求；提出借口；认罪', '1. You should get a lawyer to plead for your case. 你该请一位律师为你的案子辩护。 2. I heard him plead in court only once. 我只有一次听到他在法庭上作辩护。 3. With that kind of man you will plead in vain. 你恳求那种人将是白费力气。 4. He would see her and plead his cause again in person. 他要去见她，当面再度恳求。', '形容词: pleadable 副词: pleadingly 名词: pleader 过去式: pleaded/pled 过去分词: pleaded/pled 现在分词: pleading 第三人称单数: pleads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arbitration', '[ˌɑːrbɪ\'treɪʃn]', 'n.仲裁；公断', '1. Have you stud the arbitration award? 您研究过仲裁裁决了吗？ 2. We use arbitration to solve the dispute. 我们使用仲裁来解决这一纠纷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eligible', '[\'elɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.有资格的；合适的', '1. Mary is not eligible for an award. 玛丽没有申请助学金的资格。 2. Anyone over the age of 18 is eligible to vote. 任何年满18岁的人都有资格投票。 3. I know an eligible young lady who would be an excellent cooperator for you. 我认识一个合适的年青女士,她能成为你最称心如意的合作者。', '副词: eligibly 名词: eligibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('monumental', '[ˌmɑːnju\'mentl]', 'adj.纪念碑的；作为纪念的；不朽的', '1. Monumental heritage appears after them. 纪念碑的遗产在他们身后出现。 2. I have a monumental brass medal. 我有一枚有纪念意义的铜牌。 3. The earlier characteristics is monumental and symbolic. 前期特征是纪念性和象征性。 4. It\'s an absolutely monumental waste of energy and resources. 这绝对是种对能源和资源的不朽浪费。', '副词: monumentally 名词: monumentality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infectious', '[ɪn\'fekʃəs]', 'adj.传染的；有感染力的', '1. Measles is an infectious disease. 麻疹是种传染病。 2. When you have this anthema, you are still infectious. 身上还有这种疹子就仍然有传染性。 3. Flu is an infectious disease characterized by fever, aches and pains and exhaustion. 流感是一种传染病，其特征是发热、全身疼痛和疲乏无力。 4. He expressed infectious enthusiasm to his voters. 他对他的选民表现出很有感染力的热情。', '副词: infectiously 名词: infectiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fortuitous', '[fɔːr\'tuːɪtəs]', 'adj.偶然的；幸运的', '1. The occurrence of such things is by no means fortuitous. 出现这种问题绝不是偶然的。 2. We knew each other by a fortuitous meeting. 我们在一次偶然的邂逅中认识。 3. A series of fortuitous circumstances advanced her career. 一系列的幸运事使她的事业一帆风顺。', '副词: fortuitously 名词: fortuitousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('improvident', '[ɪm\'prɑːvɪdənt]', 'adj.不顾将来的；无远见的；不节约的；不经济的', '1. You will pay for your improvident and undisciplined behavior. 你会为自己轻率任性的行为付出代价的。 2. Her improvident speech at the meeting has set a stone rolling. 她在会上的发言缺乏远见，已产生严重后果。 3. He must bear the consequences of his improvident action. 他必须对自己挥霍浪费所造成的后果负责。 4. Mining likewise was carried on in the most superficial and improvident fashion and consequently the maximum of labor yielded but a minimum of result. 矿业也是在最肤浅而不经济的方式下进行，因此在极大的劳力中获取微小的成果。', '副词: improvidently 名词: improvidence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tactics', '[\'tæktɪks]', 'n.策略；战术', '1. Different circumstances call for different tactics. 不同的情势需要不同的策略。 2. We should adopt flexible tactics for the moment. 目前我们应该采取弹性的策略。 3. He applied bait-and-switch tactics in business. 他经商的策略是先引诱顾客来,再改变货物的品质。 4. An army commander must be skilled in tactics. 一名军事指挥官必须精通战术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('calculus', '[\'kælkjələs]', 'n.微积分；算法；结石', '1. It\'s been awhile since I did calculus. 我学微积分已经有一段时间了。 2. I had studied calculus before I got into college. 我在上大学以前,已经学过微积分。 3. Calculus is over the heads of most students. 微积分对大多数学生来说太难学了。 4. This is a problem where calculus won\'t help at all. 对于这一题，微积分一点也用不上。', '名词复数: calculi');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pharmacy', '[\'fɑːrməsi]', 'n.药房；药剂学', '1. Please go to emergency pharmacy for your medicines. 请到急诊药房取药。 2. He is a shop assistant at a Chinese pharmacy. 他是中药房的售货员。 3. He just was engaged in the pharmacy 16 years old. 他十六岁就从事药学。 4. Clinical pharmacy is a new specialty in China. 临床药学在我国是个新兴的专业。', '名词复数: pharmacies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rebellion', '[rɪ\'beljən]', 'n.叛乱；反抗', '1. The rebellion was soon stamped on by the army. 军队很快平息了叛乱。 2. The rebellion was crushed by government forces. 政府军已把叛乱镇压下去。 3. The government has just put down a rebellion. 这个国家刚刚镇压了一场叛乱。 4. The people would rise in open rebellion if oppressed by a monarchy. 如果遭到君主制的压迫，人民就会起来反抗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('facility', '[fə\'sɪləti]', 'n.设备；设施；才能；资质；灵巧；熟练', '1. The college has excellent sporting facilities. 这所学院有极好的体育设备。 2. There are few recreational facilities in our school. 我们学校里几乎没有什么娱乐设施。 3. He has great facility in learning languages. 他很有学习语言的才能。 4. I learn to use with more and more facility the pencil, brush, and graver. 我学会越来越灵巧地运用铅笔、画笔和雕刻刀。', '名词复数: facilities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extend', '[ɪk\'stend]', 'v.延伸；延长；伸展；扩展；提供；使竭尽全力', '1. Our playing fields extend as far as those trees. 我们的操场延伸到那些树前。 2. Theoretically, a line can extend into infinity. 从理论上来说直线可以无限地延伸。 3. How to extend a visa if it expires? 签证到期后怎样延长签证? 4. Dry-cleaning can extend the life of your clothing. 干洗可以延长衣服的使用寿命。', '形容词: extendable 名词: extendibility 过去式: extended 过去分词: extended 现在分词: extending 第三人称单数: extends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('magnify', '[\'mæɡnɪfaɪ]', 'v.放大；夸大', '1. I want to magnify my mother\'s picture. 我想放大我母亲的照片。 2. Magnify the magnitude of the magnetism. 放大磁性的大小。 3. He is inclined to magnify difficulties. 他老是爱夸大困难。 4. These groups and individuals magnify hate crimes by blacks in order to back their social agenda. 这些团体和个人为了给自己提出的社会议题造舆论而极力夸大黑人的攻击性犯罪。', '过去式: magnified 过去分词: magnified 现在分词: magnifying 第三人称单数: magnifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stable', '[\'steɪbl]', 'adj.稳定的；安定的；可靠的 n.马棚；马厩；一批人 v.使（马）入厩；入马棚', '1. Markets are flourishing and prices are stable. 市场繁荣, 物价稳定。 2. In order that our country could flourish and achieve its own goals, a stable environment within the country is definitely not dispensable. 国家要发展，要实现自己的目标，这是必不可少的条件，就是要国内有安定的环境。 3. The Sunnis hold a majority in four provinces and any government will have to respect them if they wish to administer a stable state. 逊尼派在四个省份里都是多数群体，而任何政府只要想管理一个安定的国家，就不得不对他们予以尊重。 4. He is a bit neurotic, but his wife is a very stable person. 他有点神经质，但他的妻子是一个非常稳重的人。 5. The horse in the stable has broken out. 马厩里的那匹马跑了。 6. Where do you stable your pony? 你那匹矮种马养在哪儿?（《牛津高阶英汉双解词典》）', '副词: stably 比较级: stabler 最高级: stablest 名词: stableness 过去式: stabled 过去分词: stabled 现在分词: stabling 第三人称单数: stables');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compose', '[kəm\'poʊz]', 'v.作曲；创作；编排；形成；使镇静', '1. She began to compose songs at an early age. 她还很年轻时就已经开始创作歌曲。 2. He was composing at the piano at the age of seven. 他7岁时就会钢琴作曲。 3. He sat down and composed a letter of resignation. 他坐下来,写了一封辞职信。 4. It is the law-makers\'s duty to compose laws into a coherent system. 将各项法律编排成为一个连贯的体系是立法者的职责。', '过去式: composed 过去分词: composed 现在分词: composing 第三人称单数: composes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('basin', '[\'beɪsn]', 'n.脸盆；盆地；流域；水池', '1. This basin is made of iron. 这个盆子是铁做的。 2. He washed his hands in a basin. 他在盆里洗了手。 3. He first poured some water in the basin. 他先在脸盆里倒了一些水。 4. Wenshui lies in the west of Taiyuan Basin. 文水位于太原盆地以西。', '形容词: basinal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pronounced', '[prə\'naʊnst]', 'adj.显著的；断然的；明确的 动词pronounce的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Age has made a pronounced change in his appearance. 岁月明显地改变了他的外貌。 2. He spoke with a pronounced English accent. 他说话带着浓重的英国口音。 3. He is a man of pronounced opinions. 他是个有坚定意见的人. 4. He has very pronounced ideas on everything. 他对每样事情都有明确的看法。 5. The two words are spelled differently, but pronounced the same. 这两个字拼写不同，但发音相同。', '副词: pronouncedly 名词: pronouncedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pensive', '[\'pensɪv]', 'adj.沉思的；愁眉苦脸的', '1. He subsided into a pensive state. 他陷入了沉思。 2. The painting can inspire a pensive mood. 这幅画能引人沉思。 3. She looked pensive when she heard the news. 她听到这消息时神情严肃. 4. The woman in this painting has a pensive smile. 这幅画上的女人脸上露出忧郁的微笑。', '副词: pensively 名词: pensiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('haste', '[heɪst]', 'n.急速；急忙 v.匆忙；赶快', '1. The more haste, the less speed. 欲速则不达。 2. In his haste, he forgot to bring his glasses with him. 匆忙之中，他忘了带眼镜。 3. She made haste to open the door. 她急忙打开门。 4. They acted with precipitate haste. 他们鲁莽仓促地采取了行动。 5. We advised him against acting in haste. 我们劝他不要匆忙行事。', '过去式: hasted 过去分词: hasted 现在分词: hasting 第三人称单数: hastes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('charitable', '[\'tʃærətəbl]', 'adj.仁慈的；(为)慈善事业的；宽恕的', '1. Acting under the cloak of charity, he made a good income for himself from the gifts of charitable people. 他打着办慈善事业的幌子，用慈善家们的捐献中饱私囊。 2. Charity is a kind of salvation, and now it\'s even more to charity as the spirit of self-redemption, to participate in charitable initiative getting higher and higher. 慈善是一种救赎，如今的人们更把慈善作为自我精神的救赎，参与慈善事业的积极性越来越高。', '副词: charitably 名词: charitableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('curiosity', '[ˌkjʊri\'ɑːsəti]', 'n.好奇心；好奇；稀奇的人或物', '1. The child showed a healthy curiosity. 那孩子有好奇心，这是好现象。 2. Her curiosity was piqued. 她产生了好奇心。 3. I had to explain the reasons to satisfy his curiosity. 我只好解释原因来满足他的好奇心。 4. The rumors excite her curiosity. 谣言引起了她的好奇心。', '名词复数: curiosities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invertebrate', '[ɪn\'vɜːrtɪbrət]', 'n.无脊椎动物 adj.无脊椎的', '1. Insects and worms are all invertebrates. 昆虫和蠕虫都是无脊椎动物。 2. Half of all invertebrate species live in tropical rain forests. 一半的无脊椎动物物种生活在热带雨林中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exultant', '[ɪɡ\'zʌltənt]', 'adj.非常高兴的；欢腾的', '1. Intense and especially ecstatic or exultant happiness. 欢欣，喜悦，高兴强烈的喜悦，尤指狂喜或欢腾的喜悦', '副词: exultantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('magma', '[\'mæɡmə]', 'n.岩浆；糊剂', '1. Magma extravasated as pressure built under ground. 当地底下的压力生成时，岩浆喷发。 2. If the magma breaks through to the surface,the result is a volcano. 如果岩浆冲出地面火山就爆发了。', '形容词: magmatic 名词复数: magmata');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brochure', '[broʊ\'ʃʊr]', 'n.小册子，资料手册', '1. I\'ll send you a brochure. 我给你一份小册子。 2. The computer\'s features are detailed in our brochure. 该计算机的特点在我们的小册子中有详细介绍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alleviate', '[ə\'liːvieɪt]', 'vt.减轻；使 ... 缓和', '1. They alleviated the boredom of waiting by singing songs. 他们以唱歌来减轻等候的厌烦。 2. The doctor gave her an injection to alleviate the pain. 医生给她注射以减轻疼痛。 3. This medicine will alleviate your sore throat. 这种药会减轻你的嗓子痛。 4. He could only alleviate the sorrow by drinking. 他只能借酒浇愁。', '名词: alleviation 过去式: alleviated 过去分词: alleviated 现在分词: alleviating 第三人称单数: alleviates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sigh', '[saɪ]', 'n.叹气；叹息 v.叹息；惋惜', '1. When he heard the news, he uttered a sigh. 听到这消息时，他叹了口气。 2. She heaved a sigh and became lost in thought. 她叹了口气，随即陷入了沉思。 3. The old man uttered a sigh and went out. 那位老人叹息了一声,走了出去。 4. I bury my face in my hands and heave a sigh. 我掩着面叹息。 5. He sighed with despair. 他绝望地叹了口气。', '名词: sigher 过去式: sighed 过去分词: sighed 现在分词: sighing 第三人称单数: sighs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('astute', '[ə\'stuːt]', 'adj.机敏的；精明的；狡猾的', '1. But by this point, any astute businessperson has a new product waiting in the wings, ready to hit the market and revitalize his business. 但到了此时，任何机敏的业主都已经开发出新产品，准备好重新进入市场开始自己新的生意。 2. Only Parmalat\'s seemingly astute ability to rapidly grow earnings and revenues with acquisitions had placated those concerns. 不过，帕玛拉特所拥有似乎很机敏的能力，可以通过收购快速提高利润和收入，才打消市场疑虑。 3. Astute salesmen know how to invest emotionally. 精明的商人懂得如何感情投资。 4. Zhou Enlai was too astute to rail against reality. 周恩来是一个非常精明的人，他不会诅咒现实。', '副词: astutely 名词: astuteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sufficient', '[sə\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.足够的；充分的', '1. The money I have saved is sufficient for buying a car. 我所存的钱足以买一辆汽车。 2. I doubt whether they really have sufficient manpower. 我怀疑他们是否真有足够的人力。 3. There is sufficient food for everybody. 有足够的饭菜供大家吃。 4. We must work hard, but equally we must get sufficient rest. 我们必须努力工作,但同时也要有充分的休息。', '副词: sufficiently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impeccable', '[ɪm\'pekəbl]', 'adj.无懈可击的；无瑕疵的', '1. Your English is impeccable! 你的英语十分好！ 2. He was proud of his impeccable pedigree. 他为他出身于名门望族而骄傲。 3. He was proud of his impeccable good manners. 他为自己无可挑剔的端庄举止而感到自豪。 4. From this we can see her impeccable moral integrity. 从这件事上，我们看到了她白璧无暇的美好心灵。', '副词: impeccably 名词: impeccability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amino', '[\'æmɪnoʊ]', 'adj.氨基的 pref.表示“氨基”', '1. This chemical is an amino acid called L-theanine. 这种化学物质是一种叫做L-茶氨酸的氨基酸。 2. Is the amino acid in honey acidity? 蜂蜜中的氨基酸是酸性的吗？ 3. There are many amino acids that the body cannot synthesize itself. 有许多种氨基酸人体自身不能合成。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appreciate', '[ə\'priːʃieɪt]', 'vt.欣赏；赏识；感激；领会；意识到 vi.增值', '1. I really appreciate his complete absorption in his work. 我很欣赏他对工作的极端专注。 2. I\'ve decided to learn photography in order that I may better appreciate the beauty of nature. 我决定学摄影以便能更好地欣赏自然的美。 3. Very few people really appreciate his works. 没人赏识他的作品。 4. His talents are not fully appreciated in that company. 他的才干在那家公司未受到充分赏识。 5. Land will continue to appreciate. 土地将继续增值。', '形容词: appreciatory 名词: appreciator 过去式: appreciated 过去分词: appreciated 现在分词: appreciating 第三人称单数: appreciates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rhythm', '[\'rɪðəm]', 'n.节奏；节律；（事件或过程）有规律的反复出现', '1. The song has a syncopated rhythm in the jazz version. 这首歌曲改编为爵士乐後采用了切分音节奏。 2. Stress and rhythm are important in speaking English. 说英语时，重音和节奏是很重要的。 3. He is trying to play the same tune in a different rhythm. 他正试图用不同节奏演奏同一个曲子。 4. The rhythm of her heart beating is normal. 她的心跳节律是正常的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inviting', '[ɪn\'vaɪtɪŋ]', 'adj.吸引人的；诱人的 动词invite的现在分词.', '1. The display in the shop window is very inviting. 那橱窗里的陈设很招揽顾客。 2. The most inviting building on our campus is the student recreation center. 我们校园里最吸引人的建筑物就是学生活动中心。 3. The food on the table looks inviting. 桌上的食物看上去令人垂涎。 4. An inviting smell of coffee wafted into the room. 一股诱人的咖啡香味飘进了房间。 5. You are just inviting trouble if you do that. 你那么做就是在自找麻烦。', '副词: invitingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nominee', '[ˌnɑːmɪ\'niː]', 'n.被提名的人；名义人', '1. The Director is awaiting the Board\'s affirmation of his nominee. 董事长在等待董事会批准他提名的候选人。 2. In fact, there has not been a nominee in several generations who has brought the depth of judicial experience to this job that she offers. 事实上，几代人以来没有哪个被提名的人能够象她这样给这个工作带来具有如此深度的司法经验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eschew', '[ɪs\'tʃuː]', 'vt.避开；回避；戒绝', '1. Plenty of companies eschew such corporate programmes. 相当多的公司避开这种公司计划。 2. They must take the vow of absolute continence and eschew all thought of greed and lust. 他们必须发誓要绝对禁欲，避开所有贪婪和欲望的想法。 3. Even companies that eschew formal open-source licenses engage in open practices in order to attract outside developers and business partners. 为了吸引外部开发者和商业伙伴，甚至那些回避开源许可证的公司也参与开放实践。', '名词: eschewal 过去式: eschewed 过去分词: eschewed 现在分词: eschewing 第三人称单数: eschews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defense', '[dɪ\'fens]', 'n.防卫；防卫物；辩护 vt.防守', '1. We must gear up industry to meet defense needs. 我们必须促进工业生产，以适应防卫的需要。 2. The magazine\'s disclosure of defense secrets caused great attention. 该杂志对防务内幕的透露引起了极大的关注。 3. The Senate has voted to support the President\'s defense plans. 参议院已经投票支持总统的防卫计划。 4. Good strong locks are the best defense against burglars. 坚固的锁是防盗贼的最好防御物。 5. The defense was overwhelmed by superior numbers. 防守被优势的兵力摧垮了。', '形容词: defenseless 副词: defenselessly 名词: defenselessness 过去式: defensed 过去分词: defensed 现在分词: defensing 第三人称单数: defenses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mask', '[mæsk]', 'n.伪装；面罩；面具；[计算机]掩码 v.掩饰；戴面具；遮盖', '1. They did so under the mask of charity. 他们是打着慈善的幌子这么做的。 2. He longed to throw off the mask of respectability. 他渴望丢掉那副道貌岸然的伪装。 3. Her sociable manner is really a mask for a very shy nature. 她那好交际的作风，实际上是她腼腆天性的伪装。 4. The bank robber wears a stocking mask. 那个抢劫银行的匪徒戴着长筒袜面罩。 5. Her smile masked true feelings. 她的微笑掩饰了她的感情。', '形容词: maskable 过去式: masked 过去分词: masked 现在分词: masking 第三人称单数: masks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quell', '[kwel]', 'vt.压制；平息；消除；减轻', '1. Soldiers were sent in to quell the riots. 已派士兵去镇压动乱。 2. The armed force had to be called out to quell violence. 不得不出动军队来镇压暴力行动。 3. His actio have done little to quell the eculation. 他的行动无助平息传言。 4. The police have been called in to quell a minor disturbance. 警察奉命出动以平息一场小规模的骚乱。', '过去式: quelled 过去分词: quelled 现在分词: quelling 第三人称单数: quells');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allegory', '[\'æləɡɔːri]', 'n.寓言；讽喻；寓意', '1. The film is an iconoclastic allegory. 电影是一个关于破坏的寓言。 2. He opens his prophecy by describing a plague of locusts, an allegory of the disasters to come upon a faithless people. 他首次预言是关于蝗虫的灾害，这是一则对无信仰的人的灾难的寓言。 3. Let me share with you a beautiful allegory. 让我与您分享一个美好的讽喻。 4. This is relayed to Montag as an allegory of society. 孟泰格将此视作社会的讽喻。', '名词: allegorist 名词复数: allegories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rational', '[\'ræʃnəl]', 'adj.合理的；理性的；能推理的 n.有理数', '1. Your choice was perfectly rational under the circumstances. 在那种情况下,你的选择是相当合理的。 2. Man is a rational being. 人是有理性的生物。 3. No rational person would go to work in his pyjamas. 任何神智正常的人都不会穿着睡衣去上班。 4. The rational numbers also fit into this scheme. 有理数也适用于这个图形。', '副词: rationally 名词: rationalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lead', '[liːd]', 'v.引导；领先；带领；过 ... (的生活)；导致 n.领头位置；主角；榜样；引言；铅', '1. She led the way downstairs for us. 她引着我们下楼。 2. Our football team leads them by two goals. 我们的足球队比他们领先两分。 3. It\'s up to you to lead us through the difficulties. 就靠你来带领我们度过难关了。 4. They lead a busy and colourful life on the campus. 他们在大学里过着忙碌而又丰富多彩的生活。 5. She always takes the lead when we plan to do something. 我们不管打算做什么事的时候总由她来领头。', '过去式: led 过去分词: led 现在分词: leading 第三人称单数: leads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('republic', '[rɪ\'pʌblɪk]', 'n.共和国；共和政体', '1. He was one of the architects of the republic. 他是这个共和国的缔造者之一。 2. Back to our Republic of Singapore. 回到我们新加坡共和国。 3. In what ways is a republic more desirable than a principality? 共和政体为何比君主政体更令人向往？ 4. In a republic, that paradise of debility, the politician is a petty tyrant who obeys the laws. 在一个共和政体，那是衰弱者的天堂，政治家是一个服从法律的小暴君。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('harmony', '[\'hɑːrməni]', 'n.和谐；协调；调和；和声', '1. An enterprise should be full of fairness and harmony. 一个企业内部应该充满公平与和谐。 2. Their life is a natural harmony. 他们的生活是一种自然的和谐。 3. There was not much harmony in international affairs during those years. 那些年国际事态不很协调。 4. Almost unconsciously she dressed in harmony with this note of simplicity. 她简直不自觉的打扮得跟这朴素的调子很调和。', '名词复数: harmonies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disclaim', '[dɪs\'kleɪm]', 'v.放弃；否认；弃权；拒绝', '1. She disclaimed ownership of the vehicle. 她放弃了这辆车的所有权。 2. The gang disclaimed all responsibility for the explosion. 这个匪帮否认与这次爆炸事件有关系。', '过去式: disclaimed 过去分词: disclaimed 现在分词: disclaiming 第三人称单数: disclaims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('factor', '[\'fæktər]', 'n.因素；因数；因子 vt.把 ... 因素包括进去 vi.作为因素', '1. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 2. The committee\'s support is an important factor in the success of the project. 委员会的支持是该项目取得成功的一个重要因素。 3. 2, 3, 4 and 6 are factors of 12. 2、3、4 和6是12的因子。 4. A new factor appears under the integral sign. 积分号内出现了一个新的因子。', '形容词: factorable 名词: factorship 过去式: factored 过去分词: factored 现在分词: factoring 第三人称单数: factors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brilliance', '[\'brɪliəns]', 'n.才华；(色彩)鲜明；光辉；辉煌', '1. He played with great brilliance. 他的演奏显示出他卓越的才华。 2. Everyone marveled at the young writer\'s brilliance. 人人都对这位年轻作家的才华感到惊讶。 3. The moon pales the stars with her brilliance. 月光以她的光华使星星黯然失色。 4. Such child future will be a brilliance! 这样的孩子前途将是一片绚烂！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('polish', '[\'pɑːlɪʃ]', 'n.光泽；上光剂；优雅；精良 v.擦亮；磨光；推敲；完善 Polish. adj.波兰的；波兰人的；波兰语的 n.波兰语', '1. A hot plate will spoil the polish on this table. 热盘子会毁坏桌面的光泽。 2. This car polish is an effective shield against rust. 这种汽车上光蜡很有防锈作用。 3. With this polish you can give a good high gloss to the wood. 使用这种上光蜡可使木器表面极为光亮平滑。 4. Now we have a presentable great speaker whose polish reminds me of Will Smith. 现在我们能言善辩的总统，他的优雅一直让我想起了威尔史密斯。 5. I polished my buttons with a handkerchief. 我用手帕把钮扣擦亮。 6. When I awoke, a Polish man came to my room, held my hand and looked at me with friendly eyes. 当我醒来时,一名波兰人走过来,他握着我的手,亲切地望着我。 7. My spoken Polish is better than my written Polish. 我的波兰语说得比写得好。', '名词: polisher 过去式: polished 过去分词: polished 现在分词: polishing 第三人称单数: polishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hew', '[hjuː]', 'v.砍；劈；砍倒；砍成；固守；开辟 abbr.(美)卫生、教育及福利部(=Department of Health；Education；and Welfare)', '1. Then she two only stretch out, and let him hew away. 然后她就把两只手伸出来,让他砍掉。 2. He knew better than to attempt to hew rocks with razor. 他知道刀片不能劈石头。 3. He was told not to hew down that ancient tree. 他被告之不要砍倒那棵古树。 4. He hewed a canoe out of a tree trunk. 他把一根树干凿成独木舟。', '名词: hewer 过去式: hewed 过去分词: hewn/hewed 现在分词: hewing 第三人称单数: hews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('girdle', '[\'ɡɜːrdl]', 'n.腰带；围绕物 vt.以腰带束缚；在 ... 周围绕', '1. He wore a girdle of famous brand. 他系着名牌腰带。 2. The girl wore a girdle around her gym tunic. 这女孩在体操衫外束了一条腰带。 3. A thick forest girdled the castle about. 一片浓密的森林包围着城堡。', '过去式: girdled 过去分词: girdled 现在分词: girdling 第三人称单数: girdles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('precede', '[prɪ\'siːd]', 'vt.在 ... 之前；先于 vi.在前面；领先', '1. He precede his speech with a welcome to the guest. 他演讲前先对来宾表示欢迎。 2. He came in, preceded by his wife. 他和他的妻子一前一后地走了进来。 3. The we should always precede the I. 集体总应先于个人。 4. This duty should precede all others. 此项义务应该优先于其他一切义务。 5. The days that preceded were filled with activity. 前几天排满了活动。', '过去式: preceded 过去分词: preceded 现在分词: preceding 第三人称单数: precedes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mechanize', '[\'mekənaɪz]', 'vt.使机械化；用机械操作', '1. We are mechanizing rapidly. 我们正在迅速机械化。', '名词: mechanization 过去式: mechanized 过去分词: mechanized 现在分词: mechanizing 第三人称单数: mechanizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fury', '[\'fjʊri]', 'n.愤怒；狂暴；狂怒的人；泼妇 Fury. n.[罗神]复仇女神', '1. He slammed the door with a vehement fury. 他愤怒地用力把门关上。 2. He was white with fury. 他气得脸色发白。 3. In a fury, she could not speak. 她气得连话也说不出来。 4. The fury of the storm abated. 暴风雨的威力已经减弱。', '名词复数: furies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('space', '[speɪs]', 'n.空间；处所；太空；空地；空闲；空格；间隙 v.留间隔；分隔；走神；忘记', '1. There is plenty of space to move about. 这里有很大的活动空间。 2. I only have a small working space. 我只有一间很小的办公室。 3. A missile was projected into space. 导弹被发射升空。 4. It\'s easier for small car to find a parking space. 小型汽车比较容易找到停车空地。 5. Space your words when you write. 写字的时候要把字均匀地隔开。', '名词: spacer 过去式: spaced 过去分词: spaced 现在分词: spacing 第三人称单数: spaces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vanquish', '[\'væŋkwɪʃ]', 'v.征服；克服；击败', '1. It is no honor for an eagle to vanquish a dove. 老鹰胜鸽,不足为荣。 2. Our army has vanquished the enemy. 我们的军队已经彻底击败了敌人。', '形容词: vanquishable 名词: vanquisher 过去式: vanquished 过去分词: vanquished 现在分词: vanquishing 第三人称单数: vanquishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('silly', '[\'sɪli]', 'adj.愚蠢的；琐屑的；可笑的；犯晕的 n.（通常指小孩子）淘气鬼；傻孩子', '1. The silly ending robs the plot of any credibility. 这愚蠢的结尾使得整个情节变得一点都不可信。 2. Don\'t get upset over silly things that people say. 不要在意人们的闲言碎语。 3. I look pretty silly in this dress. 我穿这条裙看上去很可笑。 4. I took a swing at him and knocked him silly. 我挥拳打了他一下, 把他打得晕头转向。 5. Listen, silly, we have to leave now. 听着,小淘气鬼,我们现在得走了。', '副词: sillily 比较级: sillier 最高级: silliest 名词: silliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ribbon', '[\'rɪbən]', 'n.缎带；带状物；色带 vt.用丝带装饰；撕碎', '1. She wears a ribbon belt round her waist. 她在腰部束了一条缎带。 2. She wore yellow ribbons in her hair. 她头发上戴着黄色缎带。 3. Ribbon hung from the bride\'s bouquet was tied in a bow. 从新娘的花束上垂下来的丝带打成了一个结。 4. I had to change the typewriter ribbon. 我不得不换掉打字机的色带。 5. We decorated our car lavishly,with ribbon. 我们花了一大笔钱用丝带装饰汽车。', '形容词: ribbony 过去式: ribboned 过去分词: ribboned 现在分词: ribboning 第三人称单数: ribbons');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thorough', '[\'θɜːroʊ]', 'adj.彻底的；完全的；详尽的；细致深入的', '1. I gave the radio a thorough inspection before buying it. 我把收音机彻底检查了一遍才买了下来。 2. We are trying to get a thorough understanding of the government\'s fiscal policy. 我们正努力对政府的财政政策进行全面的了解。 3. She underwent a thorough examination at the hospital. 她在医院里接受了全面检查。 4. We gave our room a thorough cleaning the next day. 第二天,我们彻底地打扫了房间。', '副词: thoroughly 名词: thoroughness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ration', '[\'ræʃn]', 'n.定额；定量；配给 vt.限量供应；配给', '1. Ration is widely used in manufacturing industry. 定额是制造业中广泛使用的一个概念。 2. Have you used your ration of petrol for this week? 你用了这星期给你定量的汽油了吗? 3. The country cut the bread ration last year. 那个国家去年削减面包配给量。 4. They had to ration petrol during the war. 战时他们不得不限量供给汽油。', '过去式: rationed 过去分词: rationed 现在分词: rationing 第三人称单数: rations');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('merciful', '[\'mɜːrsɪfl]', 'adj.仁慈的；宽大的', '1. Be merciful to those who show mercy. 对仁慈的人讲仁慈。 2. The merciful king saved the young officers from death. 仁慈的国王把年青的军官从死神手中救了出来。 3. She was merciful to the prisoners. 她对犯人很仁慈。 4. Death came as a merciful release. 死神的到来算是一种幸运的解脱。', '副词: mercifully 名词: mercifulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('haughty', '[\'hɔːti]', 'adj.傲慢的；自大的；骄傲的', '1. It is hard for a haughty man to swallow his words. 要一个傲慢的人认错是很困难的。 2. The nobles treated the common people with haughty contempt. 王公贵族以不屑一顾的傲慢态度对待平民百姓。', '副词: haughtily 比较级: haughtier 最高级: haughtiest 名词: haughtiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('humid', '[\'hjuːmɪd]', 'adj.潮湿的', '1. The humid climate didn\'t agree with him. 那潮湿的气候对他不合适。 2. She thought of her humid, stuffy darkroom. 她想起了自己那间闷热潮湿的暗室。', '副词: humidly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disarray', '[ˌdɪsə\'reɪ]', 'v.弄乱；使混乱 n.无秩序；混乱', '1. The child had disarrayed the books. 孩子把书弄乱了。 2. The naughty pupils disarray the class. 顽皮的学生打乱了班上的秩序。 3. The troops fled in disarray. 部队仓皇逃散。 4. Changing offices has left my papers in complete disarray. 办公室搬迁，使我的文件全部乱了套了。', '过去式: disarrayed 过去分词: disarrayed 现在分词: disarraying 第三人称单数: disarrays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grouchy', '[\'ɡraʊtʃi]', 'adj.不高兴的；爱抱怨的', '1. Don\'t to talk to Mr. Hughes. He\'s been really grouchy these days. 休斯先生这几天不高兴的样子，少跟他说话。 2. Waiting in doctors\' offices makes me grouchy. 在候诊室等待会让我火气大。 3. Grouchy people are always complaining for no reason. 满腹牢骚的人总是毫无理由地抱怨。 4. He tends to get grouchy when he\'s tired. 他疲倦时很容易发脾气。', '副词: grouchily 比较级: grouchier 最高级: grouchiest 名词: grouchiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blessing', '[\'blesɪŋ]', 'n.祝福；祷告；幸事', '1. He called down a blessing on his head. 他祈求降福其身。 2. The blessing of the Lord be upon you all. 愿主赐福于你们大家。 3. The government has given its blessing to the new plan. 政府已经批准了这项计划。 4. This rain will be a blessing for the farmers. 对农民来说，这场雨真是一场甘霖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decade', '[\'dekeɪd]', 'n.十年', '1. Prices have risen steadily during the past decade. 在过去十年里，物价一直在上涨。 2. Several decades have elapsed since I graduated from the college. 我大学毕业已数十年了。 3. I believed that this struggle is going to go on and it might well be decided in the next decade. 我相信这一对抗还将会持续下去，并可能在下一个十年中得出结果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vehement', '[\'viːəmənt]', 'adj.感情强烈的；猛烈的', '1. They expressed a vehement protest. 他们表达了强烈的抗议。 2. He slammed the door with a vehement fury. 他愤怒地用力把门关上。 3. She made a vehement attack on the government\'s policies. 她强烈谴责政府的政策。', '副词: vehemently 名词: vehemence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dissect', '[dɪ\'sekt]', 'v.解剖；切细；仔细研究；详细分析', '1. In biology class we had to dissect a frog. 上生物课时我们得解剖青蛙。 2. In spite of this some brave scientists did dissect bodies. 尽管如此，一些勇敢的科学家仍坚持解剖人体。', '形容词: dissectible 名词: dissector 过去式: dissected 过去分词: dissected 现在分词: dissecting 第三人称单数: dissects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('useless', '[\'juːsləs]', 'adj.无用的；无效的', '1. It was an intense but useless struggle. 这是一场剧烈而无用的挣扎。 2. Please cancel the words which are useless. 请把无用的词划掉。 3. When the umpire says you are out, it is useless to argue because his decision is irrevocable. 当裁判宣布你出局时，任何辩解都是无效的，因为他的判决不可更改。', '副词: uselessly 名词: uselessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deflect', '[dɪ\'flekt]', 'v.使偏斜；转向；改变原计划', '1. The missile deflected from its trajectory. 导弹已偏离轨道。 2. The bullet hit a wall and was deflected from its course. 子弹击中墙壁而改变了方向。 3. Don\'t try to deflect me from my intention! 别想改变我的意图。', '形容词: deflectable 名词: deflector 过去式: deflected 过去分词: deflected 现在分词: deflecting 第三人称单数: deflects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('petition', '[pə\'tɪʃn]', 'n.请愿书；祈求；申请 vi.请愿；祈求 vt.向 ... 请愿，请求', '1. Many subscribers\' names are in the petition. 请愿书上有很多签名者的名字。 2. They signed a petition in support of the workers\' demands. 他们在请愿书上签名，支持工人的请求。 3. She made a silent petition to God for help. 她默默地祈求上帝给予帮助。 4. She filed a petition for divorce. 她提出了离婚申请。 5. I can petition for Junie\'s custody. 我可以申请做琼妮的监护人。 6. She petitioned her neighbor to turn down the radio. 她请求邻居把收音机关小点声。', '形容词: petitionary 名词: petitioner 过去式: petitioned 过去分词: petitioned 现在分词: petitioning 第三人称单数: petitions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('banquet', '[\'bæŋkwɪt]', 'n.宴会 vi.参加宴会 vt.宴请；设宴', '1. The manager was called on to speak at the banquet. 经理应邀在宴会上讲了话。 2. He met the foreign friends and gave a banquet in their honour. 他会见了外国朋友，并设宴招待了他们。 3. The president gave the Prince and his attendants a farewell banquet. 总统为王子和他的随员举行了告别宴会。 4. We gave him a farewell banquet yesterday. 我们昨天为他举行了告别宴会。 5. It\'s interesting for me to banquet. 对我来说参加宴会很有意思。 6. They banqueted her like a queen when she became director of that company. 她成为公司的董事后，他们把她当成女王般设宴款待她。', '名词: banqueter 过去式: banqueted 过去分词: banqueted 现在分词: banqueting 第三人称单数: banquets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mercantile', '[\'mɜːrkəntaɪl]', 'adj.贸易的；商业的', '1. San Francisco and New York are important mercantile ports in America. 旧金山和纽约是美国重要的贸易港口。 2. I\'ve never seen you since at that mercantile evening last year. 自从去年的商务晚会以后我就没有再碰见你了。 3. The mercantile exchange led the push into electronic trading in the early 1990’s. 在20世纪90年代前期，商业交易所就推动电子交易。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('burnish', '[\'bɜːrnɪʃ]', 'v.磨光；使光亮 n.光泽；抛光', '1. He is burnishing the knife. 他正在磨刀。 2. The copper has been burnished. 铜已被抛光。 3. Such bipartisanship will do something to burnish his reputation as a reformer. 这样的两党合作将对凸显作为改革者的声誉有益。 4. Scagliola diaphaneity is bad, and without burnish. 人造大理石透明度不好，而且没有光泽。', '名词: burnisher 过去式: burnished 过去分词: burnished 现在分词: burnishing 第三人称单数: burnishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interrogate', '[ɪn\'terəɡeɪt]', 'v.质问；讯问；审问', '1. I decide to interrogate the abductors. 我决定去质问那帮绑架犯。 2. The judges may interrogate the defendant. 审判人员可以讯问被告人。 3. Now we shall interrogate you according to law. 我们现在依法对你进行讯问。 4. Mason decides to interrogate Penticoff himself. 梅森决定亲自审问彭蒂科夫。', '形容词: interrogational 名词: interrogation 过去式: interrogated 过去分词: interrogated 现在分词: interrogating 第三人称单数: interrogates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('believer', '[bɪ\'liːvər]', 'n.信徒；相信者', '1. I am a believer with religious faith. 我是个宗教信徒。 2. He still proclaims himself a believer in that theory. 他依然声称自己相信那种理论。 3. I\'m not a great believer in taking regular physical exercise. 我对经常锻炼身体的好处有点怀疑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unruly', '[ʌn\'ruːli]', 'adj.难控制的；无法无天的；任性的', '1. They are unruly mob. 他们是些难以控制的暴徒。 2. The unruly students mocked their teacher. 这群无法无天的学生嘲笑老师。 3. The unruly crowd became even more boisterous when he tried to quiet them. 他试图使那些横蛮任性的人们安静下来，可他们却吵嚷得更加厉害。', '比较级: unrulier 最高级: unruliest 名词: unruliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deride', '[dɪ\'raɪd]', 'v.嘲笑；愚弄', '1. He derides her naive attitude. 他嘲弄她天真的态度。 2. They derided his efforts as childish. 他们嘲笑他的做法很幼稚。 3. No one has the right to deride the disadvantage of handicapped people. 任何人都没有权利嘲笑残疾人的不利条件。', '副词: deridingly 名词: derider 过去式: derided 过去分词: derided 现在分词: deriding 第三人称单数: derides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sentimental', '[ˌsentɪ\'mentl]', 'adj.感伤的；感情的；多愁善感的', '1. The novel is sentimental twaddle. 这部小说纯粹是无病呻吟。 2. She\'s too sentimental about her cat. 她对她的猫未免太牵肠挂肚了。 3. She did it for sentimental reasons. 她出于情感的缘故做了此事。 4. He has a sentimental attachment to his birthplace. 他对他的出生地有眷恋之情。', '副词: sentimentally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accomplish', '[ə\'kɑːmplɪʃ]', 'vt.完成；实现', '1. I have accomplished a great deal in the last few months. 在过去几个月里，我完成了相当多的工作。 2. The prediction was literally accomplished. 这个预言确实实现了。 3. The role of a judge is to accomplish fairness. 法官的职责是实现公平。', '形容词: accomplishable 名词: accomplisher 过去式: accomplished 过去分词: accomplished 现在分词: accomplishing 第三人称单数: accomplishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pregnant', '[\'preɡnənt]', 'adj.怀孕的；充满的；意味深长的', '1. How long has she been pregnant? 她怀孕多久了？ 2. She got pregnant and was turned out of the house by her parents. 她怀孕了，父母把她赶出了家门。 3. Women who do not ovulate regularly have difficulty in becoming pregnant. 妇女排卵期不正常就不易受孕。 4. He is a man pregnant with ideas. 他是一个思想丰富的人。', '副词: pregnantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('available', '[ə\'veɪləbl]', 'adj.可利用的；可得到的；有空的；有效的；<贬>【政】有资格的，适合的', '1. Do you have a room available? 你们有空房间吗？ 2. The swimming pool is available only in summer. 这个游泳池只在夏天开放。 3. All sorts of lamps are available in that shop. 在那家商店可买到各式各样的灯具。 4. The Prime Minister was not available for comment. 首相无暇作出评论。', '副词: availably 名词: availability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pyramid', '[\'pɪrəmɪd]', 'n.金字塔；棱锥体；[证券]金字塔式交易法 v.急速增加；以金字塔的模型构建', '1. Egypt is famous for its grand pyramid. 埃及以巨大的金字塔闻名。 2. Lagrange is the lofty pyramid of mathematical sciences. 拉格朗日是数学科学中高耸的金字塔。 3. A pyramid provides a useful conceptual model for organizing scientific knowledge. 金字塔给科学知识的组织提供了一个有用的概念性模型。', '形容词: pyramidal 副词: pyramidally 过去式: pyramided 过去分词: pyramided 现在分词: pyramiding 第三人称单数: pyramids');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concurrent', '[kən\'kərənt]', 'adj.同时发生的', '1. You can\'t attend two concurrent events! 你不能同时参加两项活动！ 2. The mass murderer was given three concurrent life sentences. 那个屠杀群众的凶手被同时判处并执行三个无期徒刑。 3. He was imprisoned for two concurrent terms of 30 months and 18 months. 他被判处30个月和18个月的监禁，合并执行。', '副词: concurrently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cohesion', '[koʊ\'hiːʒn]', 'n.凝聚力；团结；内聚力', '1. These high levels of inequality erode social cohesion in the region. 这些严重的不平等侵蚀了该地区的社会凝聚力。 2. The most important thing is more cohesion within the party to win the next general election. 要想赢得下届大选的胜利,最重要的是我们党内要更加团结。 3. I had to bring some cohesion and unity into the company. 我得使整个公司恢复内聚力和统一。', '形容词: cohesive 副词: cohesively 名词: cohesiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inquisitive', '[ɪn\'kwɪzətɪv]', 'adj.好奇的；爱打听的；求知欲强的', '1. He surveyed me with an inquisitive look. 他以好奇的眼光仔细地打量我。 2. Primates are alert, inquisitive animals. 灵长目动物是机灵、好奇的动物。 3. She was very inquisitive about other people\'s affairs. 她太爱打听别人的私事。 4. Don\'t be so inquisitive. 别那么爱管闲事。', '副词: inquisitively 名词: inquisitiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('utmost', '[\'ʌtmoʊst]', 'adj.极度的；最大限度的 n.极限；最大可能', '1. He had the utmost respect for his teachers. 他极度尊敬他的老师。 2. His giving up has put us in a position of the utmost difficulty. 他的放弃已经把我们置于一个极度困难的境地。 3. The train was crowded to the utmost capacity. 火车拥挤到了最大限度。 4. The bus was already filled to its utmost limit. 这辆公共汽车乘坐人数已达到最大限额。 5. That was the utmost we could do. 那是我们能做的极限。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confiscate', '[\'kɒnfɪsˌkeɪt]', 'v.没收；充公', '1. We\'ll have to confiscate this object. 我们要没收这些物品。 2. The present policy of our Party is still to reduce rents, not to confiscate land. 目前我党方针，仍然是减租而不是没收土地。', '形容词: confiscatory 名词: confiscation 过去式: confiscated 过去分词: confiscated 现在分词: confiscating 第三人称单数: confiscates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sound', '[saʊnd]', 'n.声音；嘈杂声；音乐风格；曲调；印象；感觉；海峡；鱼鳔；探针 v.听起来；感觉起来；发出声音；发音；探测深度；探询 adj.有效的；合理的；可靠的；全面的；健康的；完好的；酣睡的；严厉的 adv.酣畅地', '1. The man was gone: his footsteps made no sound. 那人走了,他的脚步没有发出一点声音。 2. I caught a curious sound in the neighboring room. 我听到隔壁房间里有奇怪的响声。 3. He plays an original jazz-gospel sound. 他演奏了一曲自己独创的爵士福音。 4. The bell gave forth a peasant, lingering sound. 钟奏起了悠扬悦耳的曲调。 5. You sound a little down in dumps. 你听起来好象情绪有点低落。 6. There are possible risks, but nonetheless, we feel it\'s a sound investment. 有可能存在危险,但是我们仍然感到这是可靠的投资。 7. He slept sound in his mother\'s cradle song. 他在母亲唱的摇篮曲中酣然入睡。', '形容词: soundable 副词: soundly 比较级: sounder 最高级: soundest 名词: soundness 过去式: sounded 过去分词: sounded 现在分词: sounding 第三人称单数: sounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('publication', '[ˌpʌblɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.出版；发行；出版物；公布；发表', '1. The publication of his book will be next month. 将在下个月出版他的书。 2. Congress has approved a new publication law. 国会已通过一项新的出版法。 3. Publication of the newspaper will discontinue at the end of June. 该报将於六月底停止发行。 4. They voted that the publication of the journal be continued. 他们投票决定继续发行那本杂志。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('etiquette', '[\'etɪket]', 'n.礼仪；礼节；规矩', '1. The rules of etiquette are not so strict nowadays. 如今的礼仪规则已不那么严格了。 2. Etiquette was considered very important in Victorian England. 英国在维多利亚时代非常注重礼仪。 3. He understands well about diplomatic etiquette. 他熟知外交礼节。 4. He dared not break the etiquette. 他不敢破坏规矩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squash', '[skwɑːʃ]', 'n.壁球；摺皱不堪；拥挤嘈杂的人群；浓缩果汁；美国南瓜 vt.压制；压扁 vi.变扁；挤进', '1. I enjoy playing tennis and squash. 我喜欢打网球和壁球。 2. The mine reduced the car to squash. 地雷把汽车炸成一堆烂铁 3. It\'s a squash with five people in this car. 五个人坐在这个小汽车里太挤了。 4. I ordered two squashes. 我要了两杯鲜果汁。 5. The government was quick to squash any hopes of reform. 政府很快消灭了一切改革的希望。 6. The fruit will squash if it is badly packed. 水果如果包装不好会被压扁的。', '名词: squasher 过去式: squashed 过去分词: squashed 现在分词: squashing 第三人称单数: squashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('figment', '[\'fɪɡmənt]', 'n.虚构的东西', '1. That Sunday is a figment of the world\'s imagination . 星期天是世界想象出来的虚构物。 2. Doctor, are you suggesting the pain is a figment of my imagination? 医生，你是说这疼痛是我想像出来的喽?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prompt', '[prɑːmpt]', 'adj.迅速的；敏捷的；立刻的 vt.激起；促进；推动；提示 vi.提示 n.提示；提示的内容 n.[商]付款期限', '1. The occasion calls for prompt action. 这场合需要迅速的行动。 2. Their prompt actions prevented the fire from spreading. 他们敏捷的行动阻止了火势的蔓延。 3. Thank you for your prompt reply to our telegram. 多谢您对我们电报的即刻答复。 4. His curiosity prompted him to ask questions . 他的好奇心激起他问许多问题。 5. Will you prompt for us at the next performance? 下场演出时你给我们提词好吗? 6. The speaker was rather hesitant and had to be given a frequent prompt by the chairman. 那个发言人讲话结结巴巴的,经常得由主席给个提示。', '副词: promptly 比较级: prompter 最高级: promptest 名词: prompter 过去式: prompted 过去分词: prompted 现在分词: prompting 第三人称单数: prompts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('degenerate', '[dɪ\'dʒenəreɪt]', 'v.退化；堕落 adj.堕落的；退化的 n.堕落的人', '1. Watching TV too much would degenerate your brain. 多看电视会使你的头脑退化。 2. His health is degenerating rapidly. 他的健康状况迅速恶化。 3. Will too much freedom make them degenerate? 太多的自由会令他们堕落吗? 4. He didn\'t let riches and luxury make him degenerate. 他不因财富和奢华而自甘堕落。 5. The thief was a degenerate member of a fine family. 那小偷是优秀家族的堕落的成员。 6. This degenerate seduced my daughter! 这个道德败坏的人勾引我的女儿！', '副词: degenerately 名词: degenerateness 过去式: degenerated 过去分词: degenerated 现在分词: degenerating 第三人称单数: degenerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('absolutely', '[\'æbsəluːtli]', 'adv.完全地；绝对地；[语]独立地 int.（表示赞同）完全正确，一点没错', '1. I trust his discretion absolutely. 我完全相信他的判断。 2. It is difficult to cross the desert by car, but not absolutely impossible. 开车穿越沙漠很难,但并非完全不可能。 3. I consider it absolutely necessary. 我认为那绝对必要。 4. Most researchers believe that, in theory, mobile phones are absolutely safe. 多数研究者认为,从理论上讲,移动电话是绝对安全的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vanish', '[\'vænɪʃ]', 'vi.消失；绝迹；不见了', '1. He seemed to vanish into thin air. 他不留痕迹地消失了。 2. Wisdom dawns when names and forms vanish. 世间一切名相消失之时，也就是智慧的开端。 3. Without it, varnish would vanish. 没有它，清漆就会消失。 4. Many types of animals have now vanished from the earth. 很多种类的动物现在已经从地球上绝迹了。', '副词: vanishingly 名词: vanisher 过去式: vanished 过去分词: vanished 现在分词: vanishing 第三人称单数: vanishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exodus', '[\'eksədəs]', 'n.大批的离去 Exodus：（《圣经·旧约》中的）出埃及记.', '1. A massive exodus of doctors is forcing the government to recruit from abroad. 大批医生的离去迫使政府从国外雇用医生。 2. Even in August, when a mass.holiday exodus leaves Milan virtually deserted, the small square outside the church bustles with activity. 即使到了八月份，当大批游客的离去使米兰变得萧条起来时，这个教堂外面的小广场上依然熙熙攘攘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vacate', '[və\'keɪt]', 'v.空出；让出', '1. You might envision passengers standing and waiting for others to vacate a seat so that they may limber up. 你能想象到乘客们站立着等待其他人空出座位，那么他们就能放松下了。', '过去式: vacated 过去分词: vacated 现在分词: vacating 第三人称单数: vacates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ponderous', '[\'pɑːndərəs]', 'adj.笨重的；笨拙的；乏味的', '1. The elephant lowered its ponderous body into the water. 大象把它那笨重的身躯浸入水里。 2. After a whole day\'s work, he walked upstairs with a ponderous, lumbering gait. 在结束一天的工作后，他迈着沉重而笨拙的步子上楼了。 3. I don\'t like his ponderous style of writing. 我不喜欢他冗长乏味的文风。', '副词: ponderously 名词: ponderousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fin', '[fɪn]', 'n.鳍；鱼翅；鳍状物；散热片；五元纸币', '1. He did not see the fin of the other. 他没有看见另外一条的鳍。 2. The fish\'s tail fin was hurt. 这条鱼的尾鳍受伤了。 3. What I ordered was braised shark\'s fin. 我点的是红扒鱼翅。 4. For constant fin width, the heat sink with the highest fins has the best thermal performance. 在固定散热片宽度的条件下，高度最高的散热片有最佳的散热效果。', '过去式: finned 过去分词: finned 现在分词: finning 第三人称单数: fins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('operate', '[\'ɑːpəreɪt]', 'v.操作；运转；经营；动手术', '1. It\'s too difficult for him to operate this new sophisticated machine. 对他来说,操作这台复杂的机器太难了。 2. The lift doesn\'t operate properly. 这台电梯运转不正常。 3. They operate three factories and a huge warehouse. 他们经营三家工厂和一个大仓库。 4. A large number of factories operate in the red. 许多工厂都是负债经营。', '过去式: operated 过去分词: operated 现在分词: operating 第三人称单数: operates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sheathe', '[ʃiːð]', 'vt.包；插入鞘；覆 =sheath.', '1. The human body needs iron to capture oxygen, copper and chromium to absorb energy, cobalt to sheathe our nerves and zinc to help our genes. 人体需要铁来捕捉氧，需要铜与铬来吸收能量，需要钴来包覆我们的神经，又仰赖锌协助基因。 2. The human body needs iron to capture oxygen, copper and chromium to absorb energy, cobalt to sheathe our nerves and zinc to help our genes. 人体需要铁来捕捉氧，需要铜与铬来吸收能量，需要钴来包覆我们的神经，又仰赖锌协助基因。', '名词: sheather 过去式: sheathed 过去分词: sheathed 现在分词: sheathing 第三人称单数: sheathes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entitle', '[ɪn\'taɪtl]', 'vt.取名为；使有权利', '1. She read a poem entitled The Apple Tree. 她读了一首题为《苹果树》的诗。 2. He entitled the book Savage Love. 他给这本书取名为《野性的爱》。 3. His services entitle him to our respect. 凭他的功劳他应受我们尊敬。 4. Your qualifications entitle you to a higher salary. 你的资格使你有权享有较高的薪水。', '名词: entitlement 过去式: entitled 过去分词: entitled 现在分词: entitling 第三人称单数: entitles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('negligence', '[\'neɡlɪdʒəns]', 'n.疏忽；不修边幅；渎职', '1. He was sharply reprimanded for his negligence. 他因玩忽职责而受到严厉的申斥。 2. The accident was due to her negligence. 这次事故是因她疏忽所致。 3. His negligence was nothing less than criminal. 他的粗心大意无异於犯罪。 4. He dressed with easy negligence. 他穿着潇洒随便。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strain', '[streɪn]', 'n.拉紧；紧张；血统；笔调；（动植物或疾病的）品种 v.拉紧；劳累；过分使用', '1. The rope finally broke under the strain. 绷紧的绳子终于断了。 2. The tugs took up the strain and the ocean liner edged away from the quayside. 拖船开始拉紧了，远洋客轮徐徐离开了码头。 3. All her senses were on the strain when the test was going on. 测试时，她所有的感官都处于紧张状态。 4. A sudden and severe strain was placed upon us by the cutting off of these supplies. 由于供给突然被切断，我们感到了沉重的压力。 5. Too heavy a load will strain the rope to its breaking point. 负载过重会把绳子拉紧到崩断的地步。', '过去式: strained 过去分词: strained 现在分词: straining 第三人称单数: strains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rebel', '[\'rebl]', 'n.反叛者；造反者；叛逆者 v.造反；反抗；反感', '1. The rebels made regular attacks on the railways. 叛军不时地袭击铁路。 2. The rebel wanted to get away from the country. 造反者想脱离国家。 3. The woman was a rebel against feudal ethics. 那个女人是封建礼教的叛逆。 4. I\'ve always been the rebel of the family. 我在家里向来是个叛逆者。 5. When a lot of people rebel, there is a rebellion. 当许多人造反时，就出现了起义。', '过去式: rebelled 过去分词: rebelled 现在分词: rebelling 第三人称单数: rebels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clipper', '[\'klɪpər]', 'n.修剪工；大剪刀；理发剪；（十九世纪的）快速帆船；移动很快的人或物', '1. You need handkerchiefs, soap and a nail clipper. 你需要手绢，肥皂和指甲刀。 2. Shall I use the clipper on the back? 要不要我用理发推子理后面的头发？ 3. The pirate ship boarded the clipper. 海盗船强行靠近快艇。 4. The length of the clipper from stem to stern is thirty-six feet. 这艘快船从船头到船尾全长36英尺。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extravagant', '[ɪk\'strævəɡənt]', 'adj.奢侈的；浪费的；过度的；大量的', '1. She\'s got very extravagant tastes. 她有很奢侈的嗜好。 2. Extravagant people never save money. 奢侈的人攒不下钱。 3. The millionaire talked cold turkey to his extravagant nephew, hinting that he might be disinherited. 那百万富翁对他挥霍无度的侄儿晓以利害，并暗示其继承权可能被剥夺。 4. She was pilloried in the press for her extravagant parties. 她的聚会十分铺张，新闻界对她大加嘲弄。', '副词: extravagantly 名词: extravagantness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('project', '[\'prɑːdʒekt]', 'n.计划；工程；项目；课题；专题研究；住房工程 v.计划；预计；设计；放映；投射；表达；突出；投掷', '1. Our project was scrubbed. 我们的计划被取消了。 2. They doubted of the feasibility of the project. 他们怀疑这个计划的可行性。 3. The project is proceeding as planned. 工程正在按计划进行。 4. We are discussing the project to establish a new national park 我们正在讨论建立一个新的国家公园的工程。 5. The government projected a tax decrease. 政府计划降低税收。', '形容词: projectable');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adroit', '[ə\'drɔɪt]', 'adj.熟练的；灵巧的；机敏的；善于…的', '1. He is adroit in handling machinery. 他对于使用机器颇为熟练。 2. He soon became adroit at steering the boat. 他很快就熟练掌握了驾船技术。 3. Let\'s meet one of the adroit artisans. 我们就要去认识一位巧手中的巧手。 4. She gave the newsman an adroit reply. 她机敏地回答了记者的问题。', '副词: adroitly 名词: adroitness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prescription', '[prɪ\'skrɪpʃn]', 'n.处方；药方；对策', '1. The doctor is writing a prescription. 医生正在开处方。 2. The doctor dispensed a prescription to his patient. 医生开处方给病人配药。 3. The prescription of drugs is a doctor\'s responsibility. 开药方是医生的职责。 4. His prescription for economic recovery was not well received. 他为经济复苏提出的对策反应不佳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compensate', '[\'kɑːmpenseɪt]', 'v.补偿；赔偿；付报酬', '1. Nothing can compensate for the loss of one\'s health. 什么都不能补偿健康受损。 2. She was compensated by the insurance company for her injuries. 她受伤后获得保险公司的赔偿。 3. You will have to compensate us for the loss. 你必须赔偿我们的损失。', '形容词: compensative 名词: compensator 过去式: compensated 过去分词: compensated 现在分词: compensating 第三人称单数: compensates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hardy', '[\'hɑːrdi]', 'adj.强壮的；勇敢的；能吃苦耐劳的；耐寒的', '1. A few hardy people swam in the icy water. 一些强壮的人在冰冷的水中游泳。 2. Only a hardy man should enter the auto race. 只有胆大的人才能参加摩托赛。 3. Camels are tough and hardy creatures. 骆驼是能吃苦耐劳的动物。 4. Their children are remarkably hardy. 他们的孩子非常能吃苦耐劳。', '副词: hardily 比较级: hardier 最高级: hardiest 名词: hardiness 名词复数: hardies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suspension', '[sə\'spenʃn]', 'n.暂停；中止；悬挂；悬浮液', '1. I think her suspension from the team was a very harsh punishment. 我认为她被暂停参加队的比赛是很严厉的处罚。 2. The conspicuous suspicious pension is in suspension. 那笔引人注目的可疑养老金被暂停发放。 3. She appealed against her suspension. 她对被停职一事已经上诉。 4. The headmaster has made a decision of suspension of a pupil from school. 校长已经做出对一名学生停学处分的决定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cable', '[\'keɪbl]', 'n.电缆；缆；索；电报 v.发电报；(通过电缆)交流；(用缆绳)固定', '1. Cable television has been around for some time now. 有线电视面世已有些时日了。 2. They are building a submarine cable tunnel. 他们正在建设一条海底电缆隧道。 3. A number of cables are needed in this project. 这项工程需要大量电缆。 4. Try replacing the cable with a known working cable. 试著以确定是工作良好的缆线替换缆线。 5. News of his death was cabled to his family. 他的死讯已电告其家属。', '名词: cabler 过去式: cabled 过去分词: cabled 现在分词: cabling 第三人称单数: cables');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('path', '[pæθ]', 'n.路线；小路；小径；轨道；路程', '1. A bullet describes a curved path in the air. 子弹在空中作曲线运动。 2. We bumped up and down along the gravel path. 我们沿砾石小路颠簸而行。 3. They went out for a walk on the gravelled path. 他们在碎石小径上散步。 4. I very much hope that this is merely a temporary phenomenon before a path could be found for emerging Asia to move again towards and adhere to financial freedom. 我衷心希望这只属暂时的现象,不久亚洲新兴市场便会重回开放金融的轨道。', '名词复数: paths');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fancy', '[\'fænsi]', 'adj.华丽装饰的；复杂的；引人注目的；时髦的；昂贵的；好的 n.喜爱；幻想；想像力 vt.想象；希望；迷恋', '1. She wants to buy a handbag, not fancy but strong. 我想买一个手提包不要花俏,而要耐用。 2. These fancy arguments befuddled us. 这些复杂的论据令我们疑惑不已。 3. All eyes were rested on the fancy car. 所有的眼神都注视那部新奇的车。 4. A fancy hairstyle will be great for a party. 参加晚会梳个时尚发型很不错。 5. The painting took his fancy, so he bought it. 这幅画被他看中了,所以他就把它买了下来。 6. I fancy they\'re getting on well with each other. 我猜想他们相处得不错。', '副词: fancily 比较级: fancier 最高级: fanciest 名词: fanciness 名词复数: fancies 过去式: fancied 过去分词: fancied 现在分词: fancying 第三人称单数: fancies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revelation', '[ˌrevə\'leɪʃn]', 'n.揭露；泄露；发觉；启示', '1. The revelation of his past lead to his resignation. 对他过去的揭露导致了他的辞职。 2. Have you read the ex-minister\'s amazing revelations in the newspaper? 你看了前任部长在报上揭露的那些惊人的事实没有？ 3. The revelation of the plot of the traitors caused their capture. 反叛者阴谋的泄露使他们被捕。 4. Her true nature was a revelation to me. 她的真实性格对我是一个新发现。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cubic', '[\'kjuːbɪk]', 'adj.立方体的；立方的', '1. This box is a cubic object. 这个盒子是个立方体。 2. The volume of this container is 20 cubic meters. 这个集装箱的体积是20立方米。 3. What\'s the cubic capacity of this engine? 这台发动机的立体容积是多少？', '副词: cubicly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infrared', '[ˌɪnfrə\'red]', 'adj.红外线的 n.红外线', '1. Infrared cameras can also make false positives. 红外线摄影机也会判断错误。 2. The bathroom could be warmed by an infrared lamp. 可以使用红外线灯来温暖那间浴室。 3. The gunsight has an infrared lens for night vision. 射击瞄准器装有用于夜间视力的红外线镜头。 4. What are infrared and ultraviolet rays? 什么是红外线和紫外线？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('paddle', '[\'pædl]', 'n.桨；划桨；明轮翼 v.划桨；戏水；抚弄', '1. The butter churn has two paddles to whip the cream. 奶油制造机有两根搅棍搅打奶油。 2. He dipped his paddle without a splash. 他把他的短桨浸没有飞溅声。 3. Each man has a paddle for an hour and then a rest. 每个人划一个小时,然后休息一下。 4. He would himself paddle me off to the ship. 他愿亲自划船把我送上大船。', '名词: paddler 过去式: paddled 过去分词: paddled 现在分词: paddling 第三人称单数: paddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fabricate', '[\'fæbrɪkeɪt]', 'v.编造；虚构；制造', '1. The defense accused police of fabricating evidence. 被告指责警察编造证据。 2. The story was fabricated and completely untrue. 这故事是捏造的，一点不真实。 3. It is not easy to fabricate DNA evidence. 要假造染色体为证是不容易的。 4. The finest crafts people fabricated this golden ring. 这枚金戒指是由最优秀的工匠制作的。', '名词: fabrication 过去式: fabricated 过去分词: fabricated 现在分词: fabricating 第三人称单数: fabricates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('propagate', '[\'prɑːpəɡeɪt]', 'v.繁殖；增殖；传播；传送', '1. Most plants propagate by seed. 大多数植物靠种子繁殖。 2. Insects propagate themselves by means of eggs. 昆虫以产卵繁殖后代。 3. This kind of cell propagates faster in warm environment. 在温暖的环境中,这种细胞增殖更快。 4. We should propagate scientific ideas . 我们应该传播科学思想。', '形容词: propagable 名词: propagator 过去式: propagated 过去分词: propagated 现在分词: propagating 第三人称单数: propagates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amplify', '[\'æmplɪfaɪ]', 'v.扩大；详述；增强', '1. We must amplify our effort by working a lot harder. 我们必须更努力地工作来扩大成果。 2. The new manager wants to amplify the company. 新经理想要扩大公司。 3. A manufacturer can amplify the demand of a product by advertising widely. 厂商能用大做广告的方法来扩大人们对产品的需求。 4. Please amplify your remarks by giving us some examples. 请举例详述你的话。', '过去式: amplified 过去分词: amplified 现在分词: amplifying 第三人称单数: amplifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amend', '[ə\'mend]', 'vt.修正；改进', '1. They decided to amend the bill. 他们决定修正这条议案。 2. Please amend your copy of the contract accordingly. 请将你的合同文本作相应的修正。 3. Since you insist, I must amend the letter of credit. 既然你坚持，我就只好修改信用证。 4. I would advise you to amend your manners. 我劝你改正你的态度', '过去式: amended 过去分词: amended 现在分词: amending 第三人称单数: amends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('susceptible', '[sə\'septəbl]', 'adj.易受外界影响的；易受感染的；容许…的', '1. Children are more susceptible than adults. 孩子比成人易受外界的影响。 2. Some people are susceptible to advertising. 一些人易受广告的影响。 3. The plant is not susceptible to disease. 这种植物不容易受病害侵袭。 4. Children are susceptible to various illnesses. 孩子易患各种疾病。', '副词: susceptibly 名词: susceptibleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('profess', '[prə\'fes]', 'v. 声称； 冒称； 以 ... 为业； 正式接受入教； 表明信仰', '1. They have become what they profess to scorn. 他们成了自己曾声称看不起的那种人。 2. Those who today pretend to be Christ\'s followers hypocritically profess to carry out those teachings now. 今天那些冒牌的基督教徒假惺惺地声称他们现在要实行这些教导。', '副词: professedly 过去式: professed 过去分词: professed 现在分词: professing 第三人称单数: professes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boastful', '[\'boʊstfl]', 'adj.自夸的；自负的；喜夸耀的', '1. He is boastful of his learning. 他总是夸耀自己的学识。 2. I don\'t want to sound boastful but I always finish everything on time. 我不想听起来是自负的，但是我总是按时完成每件事。 3. He is boastful of his house. 他夸耀他的房子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fulminate', '[\'fʊlmɪneɪt]', 'v.大声呵斥；强烈谴责；使爆发 n.雷酸盐；雷粉', '1. The newspapers fulminate against the crime. 报纸严厉谴责这个罪行。', '形容词: fulminatory 名词: fulmination 过去式: fulminated 过去分词: fulminated 现在分词: fulminating 第三人称单数: fulminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sponge', '[spʌndʒ]', 'n.海绵 vt.用海绵擦拭；吸收掉；抹掉', '1. The sponge soaked in the water on the desk. 海绵将书桌上的水吸了进去。 2. That child soaks up new facts like a sponge! 那孩子吸收新知识像海绵似的。 3. I like to sponge myself down in a hot bath. 洗热水澡时我喜欢用海绵擦洗全身。 4. Sponge the mud spots off the car. 用海绵擦去车上的污泥。', '过去式: sponged 过去分词: sponged 现在分词: sponging 第三人称单数: sponges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swell', '[swel]', 'v.（使）膨胀；（使）鼓起；（使）增长 n.增大；膨胀；肿胀；汹涌 adj.<口>很棒的；时髦的；一流的', '1. The hills swell gradually up from the plain. 山丘逐渐由平原膨胀起来。 2. Tom had a fall and his under lip began to swell up. 汤姆跌了一跤，下唇开始肿起。 3. The budget deficit could swell further over the next few years. 未来几年内财政赤字可能会有更多增长。 4. The groups change more swiftly, swell with new arrivals, dissolve and form in the same breath. 人群的变化越来越快，忽而随着新来的客人而增大，忽而分散后又立即重新组合。', '比较级: sweller 最高级: swellest 过去式: swelled 过去分词: swelled/swollen 现在分词: swelling 第三人称单数: swells');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equation', '[ɪ\'kweɪʒn]', 'n.相等；均衡；方程式；等式', '1. The equation of wealth with happiness can be dangerous. 把财富与幸福等同起来是很危险的 2. I can\'t make this equation come out. 我不会解这个方程式。 3. What does x represent in this equation? 这个方程式中的x代表什么? 4. The professor wrote an equation on the blackboard. 教授在黑板上写了一个等式。', '形容词: equational 副词: equationally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attempt', '[ə\'tempt]', 'v.企图；尝试 n.企图；试图', '1. He attempted to smother up the scandal about his family. 他企图掩饰有关他家庭的丑闻。 2. I would be the last to attempt to answer the question. 我是最不可能去尝试回答这个问题。 3. The enemy failed in their attempt to land on the island. 敌人在岛上登陆的企图失败了。 4. He studied hard in an attempt to pass the exam. 他努力学习试图通过考试。', '形容词: attemptable 名词: attempter 过去式: attempted 过去分词: attempted 现在分词: attempting 第三人称单数: attempts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infallible', '[ɪn\'fæləbl]', 'adj.绝无错误的；绝对可靠的', '1. None of us is infallible. 没有不犯错误的人。 2. His judgment in this matter was by no means infallible. 在这件事上他的判断决不是无可指摘的。 3. There are no infallible methods. 没有绝对可靠的方法。 4. I know an infallible cure for hiccups. 我知道一种治打嗝肯定有效的药物。', '副词: infallibly 名词: infallibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thump', '[θʌmp]', 'v.重击；怦怦跳；猛击；用拳头打 n.重击声；重打', '1. He was thumping the keys of the piano. 他重重地敲击钢琴琴键。 2. My heart was thumping with happiness. 我的心兴奋得咚咚直跳。 3. I feel pain in my head for it\'s thumping all the time. 我感到头疼，脑袋一直在不断的敲击。 4. The two boys began to thump one another 那两个男孩开始动起拳头相互对打。 5. He sat down with a thump. 他砰的一声坐下。', '名词: thumper 过去式: thumped 过去分词: thumped 现在分词: thumping 第三人称单数: thumps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gin', '[dʒɪn]', 'n.杜松子酒 n.弹棉机；轧花机；陷阱；网 v.用轧棉机去籽；用陷阱（网）捕捉', '1. I\'d like a gin and orange please. 请来一杯橙汁杜松子酒。 2. They sank a bottle of gin between them. 他们俩喝了一瓶杜松子酒。 3. The motor can run a rice husker or cotton gin. 这部马达可以推动一部碾米机或是轧花机。 4. The refined roller-type cotton gin is much more convenient to use. 经过改良的轧花机比过去好用多了。', '形容词: ginny 过去式: ginned 过去分词: ginned 现在分词: ginning 第三人称单数: gins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thrift', '[θrɪft]', 'n.节俭；节约', '1. Industry and thrift favor success. 勤劳和节俭有助于成功。 2. Thrift is engrafted in his character. 他已经节俭成性。 3. Thrift has become the prevailing practice. 节约成风。 4. A businessman must wed.efficiency to thrift. 企业家必须于效率兴节约相结合。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('responsible', '[rɪ\'spɑːnsəbl]', 'adj.有责任的；负责的；责任重大的；可靠的', '1. Who\'s responsible for the terrible mess? 谁应该对这种混乱负责？ 2. As a boy, i know, i was responsible to help her. 作为个男生,我知道,我有责任帮助她。 3. We all think of her as a responsible teacher. 我们都认为她是一位很负责的教师。 4. You are supposed to be responsible for them. 你是应当对他们负责的。', '副词: responsibly 名词: responsibleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indigent', '[\'ɪndɪdʒənt]', 'adj.贫穷的；贫困的；<古>欠缺的', '1. The town government is responsible for assistance to indigent people. 镇政府负责给穷人提供帮助。 2. I grown up in the condition, which with indigent matter but full of love. 我是在物质条件贫乏但却充满爱心的环境下长大。', '副词: indigently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insane', '[ɪn\'seɪn]', 'adj.疯狂的；精神错乱的；荒唐的', '1. Are you insane? 你疯了吗？ 2. I have an insane desire to finish that thing. 我疯狂地渴望去完成那件事。 3. That person is insane. 那人精神错乱。 4. The insane man was committed to an asylum. 那个精神失常的人被送进了精神病院。', '副词: insanely 名词: insaneness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brief', '[briːf]', 'adj.短暂的；短期的；简短的；扼要的 n.摘要；案件陈述 vt.作…的概述；（向…）简单介绍', '1. There was a brief pause in the conversation. 对话中有短暂的停顿。 2. We have a tight schedule for your brief visit. I hope you don\'t mind. 对您短暂的访问,我们为您安排的日程很紧,希望您不介意。 3. In the beginning, the teacher gave us a brief introduction about the subject. 开始时,老师给我们做了关于这门课程的简短介绍。 4. I don\'t want to keep you long, so let me be brief. 我不想浪费大家的时间,就简明扼要地讲几句吧。 5. He drew up a brief for his speech. 他起草了一份讲话的摘要。 6. The chairman will brief the Board on the most recent developments. 主席将向董事会概述最近的发展。', '副词: briefly 比较级: briefer 最高级: briefest 名词: briefer 过去式: briefed 过去分词: briefed 现在分词: briefing 第三人称单数: briefs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dismal', '[\'dɪzməl]', 'adj.阴沉的；凄凉的；暗的', '1. We were all depressed by the dismal weather. 阴沉的天气让我们都感到压抑。 2. He tossed about until the appearance of the dismal London daylight, when he sprang up desperately, and walked off to his uncle\'s lodgings in Bury Street. 他翻来复去，等到伦敦那阴沉的白天开始上曙光，便一骨碌爬了起来，前往柏利街他叔父的寓所。 3. Africa will be the highlight of an otherwise dismal year. 非洲将是这异常凄凉的一年里的亮点。 4. There was something to celebrate about amid the dismal environment on rocky Patmos. 在多岩的拔摩岛凄凉的环境中，原来也有值得庆祝的事。', '副词: dismally 名词: dismalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intensify', '[ɪn\'tensɪfaɪ]', 'vt.增强；强化；加剧', '1. You must intensify your sense of responsibility. 你必须加强责任感。 2. We need to intensify our effort to fight corruption and to prevent and eliminate its root causes. 加大治本力度，从源头上预防和治理腐败。 3. Her anger intensified. 她更加生气了。', '名词: intensification 过去式: intensified 过去分词: intensified 现在分词: intensifying 第三人称单数: intensifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ascent', '[ə\'sent]', 'n.上升；上坡路；晋升；提升', '1. This was the third phase of his ascent. 这是他上升的第三阶段。 2. They made a successful ascent of the mountain. 他们成功地登上了山。 3. The last part of the ascent is very steep. 最后一段上坡路很陡。 4. The old man had difficulty climbing the rapid ascent. 这位老人攀登这条陡峭的上坡路有困难。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('periodic', '[ˌpɪri\'ɑːdɪk]', 'adj.周期的；定期的；间歇的；完句的', '1. Long long ago, we knew the periodic motion of a planet. 很久以前, 我们就知道行星的周期运动。 2. Why are the version numbers not in any particular periodic sequence? 为什么版本号不是按照任何特定的周期序列? 3. The doctor made periodic visit to the house to see if the baby was all right. 医生定期到这家进行拜访,检查婴儿的健康。 4. There is a periodic reshuffle of our company staff. 我们公司定期有人事变动。', '副词: periodically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crew', '[kruː]', 'n.全体船员；全体乘务员；(一组)工作人员；划艇队员 v.当船员；当机务人员', '1. The ship set sail after all the crew came on board. 全体船员上船后，船就开了。 2. The crew abandoned the sinking ship. 全体船员离开了正在下沉的船。 3. The plane crashed, killing all its passengers and crew. 飞机失事了，所有乘客和机组人员都遇难了。 4. The captain piped the crew down after work. 船长吹哨让全体船员下班。', '过去式: crewed 过去分词: crewed 现在分词: crewing 第三人称单数: crews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('authentic', '[ɔː\'θentɪk]', 'adj.真正的；真实的；可信的；可靠的', '1. This is an authentic medieval sword. 这是一把真正的中世纪剑。 2. He found out the most authentic restaurants. 他找到了最正宗的餐馆。 3. The details of the costume were totally authentic. 这件古装的每个小地方都完全真实。 4. He\'s got an authentic letter by Shakespeare. 他弄到了一封莎士比亚的亲笔信。', '副词: authentically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repute', '[rɪ\'pjuːt]', 'n.名声；名气；声望 v.认为；以为', '1. He is held in high repute. 他名声很好。 2. Round 1900 his repute was still untarnished. 在1900年前后他的名声仍很响亮。 3. She is a singer with some repute. 她是个小有名气的歌手. 4. The wine is in high repute worldwide. 这酒在世界上享有盛名。', '过去式: reputed 过去分词: reputed 现在分词: reputing 第三人称单数: reputes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insinuate', '[ɪn\'sɪnjueɪt]', 'v.暗示；迂回进入；迂回进行；含沙射影的说', '1. He insinuated his doubt of her ability. 他暗示了他对她能力的怀疑。 2. He tried to insinuate himself into the boss\'s favor. 他设法巧妙地渐渐取得老板的欢心。 3. She insinuate to us that her partner have embezzle fund. 她旁敲侧击地指出她的合夥人盗用了资金。 4. I didn\'t insinuate anybody or anything. 我并未影射如何人或任何事。', '形容词: insinuative 名词: insinuator 过去式: insinuated 过去分词: insinuated 现在分词: insinuating 第三人称单数: insinuates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contradict', '[ˌkɒntrə\'dɪkt]', 'vt.反驳；与 ... 矛盾', '1. He did not contradict his attorney\'s comment. 他没有反驳律师的意见。 2. She doesn\'t like to contradict her husband in public. 她不愿在众人面前反驳她丈夫。 3. Don\'t contradict your father. 别和你父亲犟嘴。 4. The report contradicts what we heard yesterday. 这个报道与我们昨天听到的有矛盾。', '形容词: contradictable 名词: contradicter 过去式: contradicted 过去分词: contradicted 现在分词: contradicting 第三人称单数: contradicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sojourn', '[\'soʊdʒɜːrn]', 'n.旅居；逗留 v.旅居；逗留', '1. During his sojourn in Africa he learned much about native customs. 他在寄居非洲期间，学得了许多当地的风俗。 2. I was already feeling better for my sojourn here. 我在此逗留期间，觉得体力日渐恢复。 3. He should sojourn in villages and hamlets. 他应该在乡村小住数日。 4. He sojourned with a friend in Wales for two weeks. 他在威尔士一个朋友那儿住了两个星期。', '名词: sojourner 过去式: sojourned 过去分词: sojourned 现在分词: sojourning 第三人称单数: sojourns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alarm', '[ə\'lɑːrm]', 'n.警报；警报器；惊恐 vt.警告；使惊恐；向 ... 报警', '1. The proceedings were interrupted by the fire alarm. 会议的进程被火灾警报打断了。 2. The instant they heard the alarm, they fell in for action. 他们一听到警报，就立即集合准备战斗。 3. The smoke triggered off the alarm. 这些烟把警报器触响了。 4. In case of fire, ring the alarm bell. 如遇失火，请按警铃。 5. Alarm everyone quickly because the house is full of smoke. 快警告大家,屋子理都是烟。', '副词: alarmingly 过去式: alarmed 过去分词: alarmed 现在分词: alarming 第三人称单数: alarms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kidnap', '[\'kɪdnæp]', 'v.绑架', '1. Police have uncovered a plot to kidnap the President\'s son. 警方已侦破一起绑架总统之子的阴谋。 2. If you improve security at embassies, they kidnap businessmen. 如果你加强了大使馆的安全防范，他们就绑架商人。', '名词: kidnapper 过去式: kidnapped/kidnaped 过去分词: kidnapped/kidnaped 现在分词: kidnapping/kidnaping 第三人称单数: kidnaps/kidnaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flora', '[\'flɔːrə]', 'n.植物；群落 （大写）Flora：[罗神]花神弗洛拉； 弗洛拉（女名）.', '1. My professor studies flora of the Palaeozoic Era. 我的教授研究古生代的植物群。 2. Flora of clay desert is similar to that of detritus desert. 粘土荒漠上的植物和碎石荒漠上的植物相似。 3. The results indicated that allelopathic weed Solidago canadensis L. had a significant influence on the microbial flora. 结果表明，具化感作用潜力的加拿大一枝黄花明显影响了土壤中根部微生物群落多样性。 4. The humans upon Earth were primitive in nature, living from roots and plants in simple dwellings constructed from the local flora and fauna. 地球上的人类在本性上是纯朴的，以根茎和庄稼为生，在当地的植物和动物群落中构建简单的住所。 5. He had asked Flora for the Croydens\' file. 他请弗洛拉取来了克罗伊敦夫妇的文件夹。', '名词复数: floras');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flap', '[flæp]', 'n.拍打；拍打声；片状垂悬物；副翼；<口>不安 v.拍打；鼓翼而飞', '1. A flap from the tail of the whale upset the boat. 鲸尾轻轻一拍便把小船打翻了。 2. The flap of the birds drew the attention of a cat. 这群鸟不停地振翅吸引了一只猫的注意力。 3. I licked the flap of the envelope and sealed it. 我舔了舔信封盖口,把它封好。 4. I flap the flies away but soon they fly back. 我把苍蝇赶走，但一会儿又飞回来了。', '过去式: flapped 过去分词: flapped 现在分词: flapping 第三人称单数: flaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equator', '[ɪ\'kweɪtər]', 'n.赤道', '1. The equator is an imaginary line. 赤道是一条实际上并不存在的线。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('poster', '[\'poʊstər]', 'n.海报；装饰画；急行旅人', '1. The lettering on the poster is very eye-catching. 海报上的字体非常醒目。 2. The poster only stayed up a few hours before it was stolen. 那张海报贴上去没几个小时就让人给偷走了。 3. He put up a poster advertising the circus. 他贴了一张宣传马戏团的海报。 4. The poster wouldn\'t stick even though I drenched it with glue. 我涂了大量胶水，可那张海报就是贴不住。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('friction', '[\'frɪkʃn]', 'n.摩擦；摩擦力；分歧', '1. Constant friction wore out the heels of my shoes. 不断的摩擦磨损了我的鞋跟。 2. Matches are lighted by friction. 火柴由摩擦而生火。 3. Friction lowers the efficiency of a machine. 摩擦减低机器的效率。 4. Friction causes a rolling ball to stop finally. 摩擦力使滚动的球最终停了下来。', '形容词: frictional 副词: frictionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foremost', '[\'fɔːrmoʊst]', 'adj.最重要的；最初的 adv.在最前面', '1. He is one of the foremost scientists in China. 他是中国最重要的科学家之一。 2. He was one of the foremost literary scholars in England. 他是英格兰最重要的文学专家之一。 3. Good schemes will do more than funnel money from latecomers to early takers, allowing the foremost to prosper at the expense of the hindmost. 好的庞式计划将不仅仅是将钱从后来者转到早的加入者手中，以最后面的加入者为代价来使最初的加入者获得成功。 4. First and foremost, I think you should work harder on your biology. 首先，我认为你应该多在生物学上下功夫。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('selection', '[sɪ\'lekʃn]', 'n.选择；挑选；挑选出来的人或事', '1. That shop has a fine selection of cakes. 那家商店有各种精美的糕点供我们选择。 2. That store has a good selection of furniture. 那家店有很多家具可供挑选。 3. Her selection of a dress took a long time. 她挑选一件衣服花了很长时间。 4. In making the selection we passed this short piece by quite inadvertently. 在挑选时我们完全出自疏忽而漏过了这篇短文。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('curb', '[kɜːrb]', 'n.路边；克制；勒马绳 vt.抑制；勒住；牵(狗)到合适地方大小便', '1. He parked his car along the curb. 他把汽车停靠在路边。 2. I stood at the curb trying to breathe. 我站在人行道沿上想缓口气。 3. You must try to put a curb on your bad temper. 你必须学着克制自己暴躁的脾气。 4. High interest rates put a curb on spending. 高利率抑制了消费 5. I could be able to curb my desires. 我能够抑制住自己的欲望。', '过去式: curbed 过去分词: curbed 现在分词: curbing 第三人称单数: curbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opera', '[\'ɒpərə]', 'n.歌剧 n.挪威Opera软件公司的浏览器软件', '1. Have you heard the opera sung in French? 你听过用法语唱的这场歌剧吗？ 2. Opera houses were packed out whenever she was singing. 她一演唱剧院就满座。 3. That opera singer has good lungs. 那位歌剧演员声音宏亮。 4. The opera was quite stupendous. 这部歌剧很精彩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('species', '[\'spiːʃiːz]', 'n.种类；（单复同）物种', '1. He is wearing a strange species of hat. 他戴着一种奇怪的帽子。 2. There are more than 1,000 alien species in China. 中国的外来物种有1000多种。 3. The giant panda has become an endangered species. 大熊猫已成了一种濒临灭绝的动物。 4. There has been a sharp decline in the number of species. 物种数量骤然下降。', '名词复数: species');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('collapse', '[kə\'læps]', 'v.（使）倒塌；（使）崩溃；（使）瓦解；折叠 n.倒塌；崩溃；暴跌', '1. The roof collapsed under the weight of snow. 房顶在雪的重压下突然坍塌下来。 2. If you work too hard,your health may collapse. 如果你工作太累的话，你可能病倒。 3. The enterprise collapsed through lack of support. 该企业因无力支持而倒闭。 4. He collapsed the wheelchair and put it on the boat. 他将轮椅折叠起来放在船上。 5. A flood caused the collapse of the bridge. 洪水使桥倒塌了。', '形容词: collapsible 名词: collapsibility 过去式: collapsed 过去分词: collapsed 现在分词: collapsing 第三人称单数: collapses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('initially', '[ɪ\'nɪʃəli]', 'adv.最初', '1. Initially, I disagree with his proposal, but later I changed my mind. 起初我不同意他的提议，不过后来我改了主意。 2. She came initially to spend a few days, but in the end she stayed for a whole month. 起先她只打算来待几天，但後来却住了整整一个月。 3. The entire wound may not be infected initially. 整个伤口最初可能未被感染。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('originally', '[ə\'rɪdʒənəli]', 'adv.原本；起初；独创地', '1. He originally need not buy such big house. 他本来不必买这样一所大房子。 2. I had a notion that she originally came from Poland. 我有个想法认为她的原籍是波兰。 3. The idea originally emanated from his brother. 这个主意最初是他哥哥出的。 4. We originally intended to stay for just a few days. 我们起初只打算待几天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('topography', '[tə\'pɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.地志；地形学；地势；剖析图', '1. Topography seems easy to explain when beholding jagged summits such as Colorado\'s Rocky Mountains or California\'s Sierra Nevada range. 只要看看美国科罗拉多州洛矶山脉或是加州内华达山脉这些高低起伏的山峰，要解释地形学似乎不是件难事。 2. Because of the complex topography, the road has to twists through the mountain. 由于地势复杂，道路只能回绕在山间。 3. They have survived the destructive influences of man through their location in precipitous topography and the moist winter micro-climate. 由于峡谷地势峻峭，加上冬季仍保持潮湿，故林木得以保存，未受人为破坏。', '形容词: topographic 副词: topographically 名词: topograph 名词复数: topographies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bondage', '[\'bɑːndɪdʒ]', 'n.奴役；束缚', '1. They seem to love bondage more than liberty. 他们似乎喜欢被奴役胜于自由。 2. In modern time, it is easy for one to fall under the bondage of gold. 在现代社会，一个人很容易为金钱所奴役。 3. We should break the bondage of ossified thinking. 我们要冲破保守僵化思想的束缚。 4. They aim to deliver the people who are in bondage to superstitious belief. 他们的目的在于解脱那些受迷信束缚的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wrap', '[ræp]', 'v.包；裹；覆盖；隐藏 n.围巾；披肩；包装材料', '1. You should wrap up the gift in a paper. 你应该把礼物用纸包好。 2. I wrapped the rug around the sick man\'s legs to keep him warm. 我用毯子把病人的腿包了起来，让他暖和一点儿。 3. Wrap the meat in foil before you cook it. 把肉用锡箔裹起来后再烧。 4. The lid is an aluminium-covered cork bung, over-covered with a tamper-evident shrink wrap. 盖子是铝覆盖软木邦，过覆盖篡改明显收缩包装。 5. Over her shoulders was thrown a much-mended wrap. 她的肩上搭着一件补了多次的围巾。', '过去式: wrapped/wrapt 过去分词: wrapped/wrapt 现在分词: wrapping 第三人称单数: wraps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blizzard', '[\'blɪzərd]', 'n.暴风雪；大量 n.暴雪（美国游戏软件制作公司）', '1. It was sheer madness to attempt the drive during a blizzard. 试图在暴风雨中驾车绝对是极度愚蠢的 2. The blizzard blotted out the sky and the land. 暴风雪铺天盖地而来。 3. We were marooned by the blizzard. 我们为暴风雪所困。 4. The blizzard was still raging outside. 外面暴风雪仍在肆虐。 5. The QA program Blizzard uses does have a small draw back. 暴雪的质量保证体系使用一种小回溯的方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('continuation', '[kənˌtɪnjʊ\'eɪʃən]', 'n.继续；延续；续集', '1. He argued for a continuation of the search. 他主张继续搜查。 2. This road is a continuation of the motorway. 这条公路是高速公路的延伸。 3. Tune in again tomorrow to hear the continuation of our exciting story. 明天接着收听这个激动人心故事的续集。 4. This is the continuation of the story. 这是故事的后续部分。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mature', '[mə\'tʃʊr]', 'adj.成熟的；(保单）到期的；考虑周到的 v.成熟；长成', '1. This is the most mature of his plays. 这是他最成熟的一部剧作。 2. She swept her hair back, so she looks more mature than before. 她把头发往后梳，所以显得比以前成熟。 3. Your fixed account is mature and can be withdrawn any time. 您的定期存款已经到期了，随时可以提取。 4. Young as she is, she cares for others and has a mature mind. 她虽然年轻,但却很为他人着想,考虑周到。 5. Girls mature earlier than boys. 女孩比男孩成熟得早些。', '副词: maturely 比较级: maturer 最高级: maturest 名词: matureness 过去式: matured 过去分词: matured 现在分词: maturing 第三人称单数: matures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('segregate', '[\'seɡrɪɡeɪt]', 'v.分离；隔离；分凝 adj.分离的', '1. Why should the handicappedbe segregated from the able-bodied? 为什么要把伤残人士和身体健康的人分开? 2. Some societies still segregate men and women. 有的社会仍然将男女隔离。 3. Mixture of black powder and magnesium has a tendency to segregate. 黑药和镁的混合物具有离析的倾向。', '形容词: segregative 名词: segregator 过去式: segregated 过去分词: segregated 现在分词: segregating 第三人称单数: segregates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tremble', '[\'trembl]', 'n.战悚；颤抖 v.发抖；忧虑；震颤', '1. His remarks struck a tremble into her heart. 他的话令她感到不寒而栗。 2. There was a tremble in her voice. 她声音颤抖。 3. The dog was all of a tremble with cold. 这条狗冻得全身发抖。 4. He was trembling with rage. 他气得发抖。', '形容词: trembly 副词: tremblingly 名词: trembler 过去式: trembled 过去分词: trembled 现在分词: trembling 第三人称单数: trembles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cite', '[saɪt]', 'vt.引用；传讯；表扬；举(例)', '1. The lawyer cited a previous case to support his argument. 律师引用了以前的案例来支持他的论点。 2. It\'s no use citing the Bible to somebody who doesn\'t believe in God. 对不信上帝的人引用圣经的话是没用的。 3. I\'ll just cite some figures for comparison. 我要引用一些数字作比较。 4. He was cited for contempt of court. 他因蔑视法庭而被传讯。', '形容词: citable 过去式: cited 过去分词: cited 现在分词: citing 第三人称单数: cites');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pollen', '[\'pɑːlən]', 'n.花粉 vt.授粉给', '1. Ben is allergic to pollen. 班对花粉过敏。 2. Anther is a part of a flower that contains the pollen. 花药是花的雄蕊上带花粉的部分。 3. There is a high pollen count in the air. 空气中有很高的花粉计数。 4. Stamen is in the middle of a flower and may produce pollen. 雄蕊长在花的中央，能产生花粉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chromosome', '[\'kroʊməsoʊm]', 'n.染色体', '1. Chromosome studies on two species of Trifolium L. 两种车轴草的染色体研究。 2. Chromosome breaks may also lead to inversions and translocations. 染色体破裂也可能引起倒位与易位。', '形容词: chromosomal 副词: chromosomally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shrub', '[ʃrʌb]', 'n.灌木 n.果汁甜酒', '1. A rose is a perennial shrub or vine. 玫瑰是一种常青灌木或藤本植物。 2. There are many different kinds of shrub. 灌木有许多不同的种类。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('climate', '[\'klaɪmət]', 'n.气候；风气', '1. Britain has a temperate climate. 英国气候温和。 2. She adapted herself quickly to the new climate. 她很快就适应了这种新气候。 3. The small city has the climate that is changeable in the extreme. 这座小城有变化多端的气候。 4. In the current critical climate her work is not popular. 在当前评论风气影响下，她的作品不怎么受欢迎。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('uniform', '[\'juːnɪfɔːrm]', 'n.制服 adj.一致的；统一的', '1. He looks very manly in his uniform. 他穿着制服十分精神。 2. The students are wearing school uniforms. 学生们穿着校服。 3. The rows of houses were uniform in appearance. 这一排排的房屋外表都是一样的。 4. Their internal temperatures are essentially uniform with the environment. 它们的体温与周围环境基本上是一致的。', '副词: uniformly 名词: uniformity 过去式: uniformed 过去分词: uniformed 现在分词: uniforming 第三人称单数: uniforms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sensuous', '[\'senʃuəs]', 'adj.感觉上的；感觉的；激发美感的', '1. After hard work we could feel the sensuous delight of a hot bath. 在辛苦的工作后，我们能够感觉洗热水澡全身舒畅的快乐。 2. In the droop of her lip there was something sensuous. 在她那下垂的嘴唇上的确有点儿敏感的意味。 3. He likes sensuous painting. 他喜欢引起美感的绘画。 4. Art songs by Schubert give one sensuous pleasure. 舒伯特的艺术歌曲给人以美感。', '副词: sensuously 名词: sensuosity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('implicit', '[ɪm\'plɪsɪt]', 'adj.含蓄的；绝对的；无疑问的；固有的；无保留的；暗示的', '1. Her attitude was implicit in the answer she gave us. 她在给我们的答复中态度是含蓄的。 2. The system of rules implicit in a language, viewed as a mechanism for generating all sentences possible in that language. 语法规则隐含在一种语言中的规则体系，被看作在该语言中生成所有可能的语句的机制 3. The crew had implicit faith in the captain\'s judgment. 全体船员都绝对相信船长的判断。 4. The oak is implicit in the acorn. 橡实是橡树固有的。', '副词: implicitly 名词: implicitness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('injure', '[\'ɪndʒər]', 'vt.伤害；损害；损伤', '1. Don\'t injure yourself with that tool. 不要让那工具伤害到你。 2. He that spare the bad injure the good. 饶恕了恶人，伤害了好人。 3. It would naturally injure him in her estimation. 那自然也会损害到她对他的评价。 4. This rough life threatened to injure his health,but he didn\'t mind. 这种艰苦生活看来要损害他的健康，但他并不介意。', '名词: injurer 过去式: injured 过去分词: injured 现在分词: injuring 第三人称单数: injures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extreme', '[ɪk\'striːm]', 'adj.极度的；极端的 n.极端；极限', '1. Extreme cold can wake a hibernating animal. 极度的寒冷能使正在冬眠的动物苏醒。 2. The extreme heat sapped his strength and health. 极度的暑热逐渐损耗他的体力兴健康。 3. Extreme poverty had reduced them to a state of apathy. 极端的贫困使他们万念俱灰。 4. The capital is in the extreme south of the country. 首都在这个国家的最南端。 5. Love and hate are extremes. 爱和恨是两个极端。', '副词: extremely 名词: extremeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immobile', '[ɪ\'moʊbl]', 'adj.不动的；不能活动的；不变的；静止的', '1. The deer stood immobile among the trees. 那只鹿一动不动地站在树丛里。 2. His illness has left him completely immobile. 他的病使他完全丧失了活动能力。 3. It remained immobile in the centre of each screen. 它保持在各个屏幕的中央。', '名词: immobility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('debatable', '[dɪ\'beɪtəbl]', 'adj.有疑问的，有争议的；成问题的', '1. It is also a very debatable argument. 这也是个争论很大的话题。 2. It is debatable whether it is cost-effective. 它的成本效益如何，尚无定论。 3. It\'s debatable whether or not the reforms have improved conditions. 改革是否改善了现状，这问题仍有争议。', '副词: debatably');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('behavior', '[bɪ\'heɪvjə]', 'n.行为；举止；习性；态度', '1. His behavior was, in a word, shocking. 总之，他的行为是令人震惊的。 2. His behavior called forth sharp criticism. 他的行为招致尖锐的批评。 3. His strange behavior made the police suspicious. 他不寻常的举止引起了警察的怀疑。 4. Their behavior towards me shows that they do not like me. 他们对我的举止说明他们不喜欢我。', '形容词: behavioral 副词: behaviorally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immune', '[ɪ\'mjuːn]', 'adj.免疫的；免除的', '1. This patient\'s immune system has been destroyed. 这位病人的免疫系统受到了破坏。 2. I\'m immune to smallpox as a result of vaccination. 我接种过疫苗了,所以对天花有免疫力。 3. Nobody is immune from criticism. 谁都难免受批评。 4. The criminal was told he would be immune if he helped the police. 这个罪犯被告知，如果他协助警方就可以免于被起诉。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('novice', '[\'nɑːvɪs]', 'n.新手；新信徒', '1. He is a novice at swimming. 他是一个游泳新手。 2. I\'m a complete novice at skiing. 滑雪我完全是个新手。 3. The novice\'s expectation is inherently unrealistic and uninformed. 新手的期望大多是不现实和零散的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('erupt', '[ɪ\'rʌpt]', 'v.爆发；喷发；发疹', '1. Violence has erupted on the streets. 大街上突然发生了暴乱。 2. The demonstration erupted into violence. 示威游行中突然出现了武斗。 3. An active volcano may erupt at any time. 活火山随时可能喷发。 4. It\'s many years since Mount Vesuvius last erupted. 维苏威火山上一次喷发至今已有很多年了。', '形容词: eruptive 副词: eruptively 过去式: erupted 过去分词: erupted 现在分词: erupting 第三人称单数: erupts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hoarse', '[hɔːrs]', 'adj.沙哑的；嘶哑的；刺耳的', '1. The hoarse tenor singer mucked up the recital. 沙哑的男高音把音乐会搞砸了。 2. Tom whooped until he was hoarse, but it was of no use. 汤姆直喊得嗓子都哑了也无济于事。 3. We shouted ourselves hoarse at the football match. 足球比赛时我们把嗓子都喊哑了。 4. After you were gone, I heard hoarse and angry screams; 你走后,我听见一阵刺耳狂暴的嘶叫;', '副词: hoarsely 比较级: hoarser 最高级: hoarsest 名词: hoarseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disorder', '[dɪs\'ɔːrdər]', 'n.混乱；杂乱；不适；失调；疾病 vt.扰乱', '1. The meeting terminated in disorder. 会议在混乱中结束。 2. This school is completely in disorder. 这所学校完全在混乱状态当中。 3. The whole country of Hungary is in disorder right now. 整个匈牙利现在陷入了一片混乱。 4. The room is in dreadful disorder. 房间里乱七八糟。 5. A series of accidents disordered the shop. 一连串的意外事件把店里弄得乱七八糟。', '过去式: disordered 过去分词: disordered 现在分词: disordering 第三人称单数: disorders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glaze', '[ɡleɪz]', 'v.装以玻璃；上釉；变得光滑；变呆滞 n.釉；覆罩的一层', '1. There was raw glaze on the pots that sat again on the drying rack. 在干燥架上又摆上了才上釉的陶罐。 2. Tang three-color glaze horses are famous for their perfect design and realism. 唐三彩上釉马以其造型精美和形态生动而著名。 3. The glaze of the table was scratched. 桌子的釉面被刮坏了。 4. Tang three-color glaze horses are famous for their perfect design and realism. 唐三彩上釉马以其造型精美和形态生动而著名。', '名词: glazer 过去式: glazed 过去分词: glazed 现在分词: glazing 第三人称单数: glazes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('famish', '[\'fæmɪʃ]', 'v.（使）挨饿；（使）饥饿', '1. When\'s lunch? I\'m famished! 什么时候吃午饭? 我都快饿死了！ 2. The long drought famished many people. 久旱使很多人陷入饥饿。', '名词: famishment 过去式: famished 过去分词: famished 现在分词: famishing 第三人称单数: famishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discrimination', '[dɪˌskrɪmɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.歧视；鉴赏力；辨别', '1. He is passionately opposed to racial discrimination. 他极端反对种族歧视。 2. Discrimination against Blacks is still common. 歧视黑人仍是普遍现象。 3. We should not have racial discrimination. 我们不该有种族歧视。 4. You should rely on your own discrimination. 你应该相信自己的眼力。', '形容词: discriminational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fortify', '[\'fɔːrtɪfaɪ]', 'v.加强；增强；筑防御工事于；（物质或精神上）支持或鼓励', '1. They decided to fortify the coastal areas. 他们决定加强海岸地区的防卫。 2. This country will fortify the coastal areas. 该国将加强沿海地区的防御。 3. Tungsten is used to fortify steel for cars. 钨可以固化钢铁来生产汽车。 4. They fortify the dam against the flood. 他们加固堤坝以防止洪水。', '形容词: fortifiable 副词: fortifyingly 名词: fortifier 过去式: fortified 过去分词: fortified 现在分词: fortifying 第三人称单数: fortifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('needy', '[\'niːdi]', 'adj.贫穷的；缺乏的 n.贫穷的人', '1. There are many needy families in our village. 我们村子有很多贫困家庭。 2. He deems it his duty to help his needy friends. 他认为帮助穷朋友是他的义务。 3. The rich man gave much food to needy people. 那位富翁给了穷人很多食物。 4. The government has worked out a plan of succoring the needy. 政府已经制定出了救济贫民的计划。', '比较级: needier 最高级: neediest 名词: neediness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('denote', '[dɪ\'noʊt]', 'vt.表示；象征', '1. A smile often denotes pleasure and friendship. 微笑常常表示高兴和友善。 2. These nouns denote a state of joyful exuberance. 这些名词都指示洋溢着欢乐的状态。 3. Dark clouds denote a coming storm. 黑云表明风暴要来临。 4. We often denote danger by red letters. 我们常常用红字表示危险。', '形容词: denotable 过去式: denoted 过去分词: denoted 现在分词: denoting 第三人称单数: denotes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deficiency', '[dɪ\'fɪʃnsi]', 'n.缺乏；不足；缺陷；缺点', '1. I have a slight calcium deficiency. 我有点缺钙。 2. The result in either case is an energy deficiency. 不论哪种情况结果都会导致能量损失。 3. Things will go much better if people of the same trade make up the other\'s deficiency from their own surplus. 同行业之间互通有无，调剂余缺，事情就好办得多了。 4. The deficiency of this plan is very clear and it can\'t possibly succeed. 这项计划的缺陷是很明显的，它不可能成功。', '名词复数: deficiencies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('monitor', '[\'mɑːnɪtər]', 'v.监视；监督；监听 n.班长；监视器；监听员；[计算机]显示器', '1. Police officers have been closely monitoring the organization\'s activities. 警方密切地监视着该组织的活动。 2. He will monitor and review the company\'s rules and regulations. 他将监督并审查该公司的规章制度。 3. This instrument monitors the patient\'s heartbeats. 这台仪器监听病人的心跳。 4. The monitor handed the papers out to the classmates. 班长把试卷分发给同学们。', '名词: monitorship 过去式: monitored 过去分词: monitored 现在分词: monitoring 第三人称单数: monitors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relief', '[rɪ\'liːf]', 'n.减轻；解除；轻松；浮雕；救济(品)；安慰；替代 adj.提供救济的；文本的', '1. The pills gave her some relief. 药片减轻她一些痛苦。 2. This medicine will give you quick relief. 这种药将迅速解除你的病痛。 3. A doctor\'s life is consecrated to the relief of suffering. 医师的一生奉献于解除世人的疾苦。 4. His jokes provided some comic relief in what was really a dull speech. 他说的笑话给极沉闷的讲话增加几分轻松气氛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('engender', '[ɪn\'dʒendər]', 'v.产生；引起', '1. Finally, managers can use intuition to bypass in-depth analysis and move rapidly to engender a plausible solution. 最后，管理者可通过直觉绕开深奥的分析而快速产生一个可能的解决办法。 2. An unguided ramble into its recesses in bad weather is apt to engender dissatisfaction with its narrow, tortuous, and miry ways. 天气不好的时候，没有向导带路而独自漫游到谷内幽深之处的人，容易对蜿蜒其间的狭窄的泥泞小道产生不满情绪。', '名词: engenderer 过去式: engendered 过去分词: engendered 现在分词: engendering 第三人称单数: engenders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discord', '[\'dɪskɔːrd]', 'n.不调和；不一致；[音]不谐和 vi.不一致；不协调', '1. What has brought discord into the family? 什么事使得这个家庭不和？ 2. He\'s been a source of discord and worry. 他成为不和和烦恼的根源。 3. Various discords have arisen over this question. 人们在这个问题上发生了不少争执。 4. The discord of his music was hard on the ear. 他演奏的不和谐音很刺耳。 5. The speaker\'s opinion discords with the principles of this society. 演讲者的意见与本会的原则不符。', '过去式: discorded 过去分词: discorded 现在分词: discording 第三人称单数: discords');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cursory', '[\'kɜːrsəri]', 'adj.匆匆忙忙的；草率的；粗略的', '1. He had given the report a cursory reading. 他草草看了一遍这份报告。 2. He signed with only a cursory glance at the report. 他只草草看了一眼报告就签了名。 3. After a cursory examination, he was released. 经过粗略的检查，他被释放。', '副词: cursorily 名词: cursoriness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('surge', '[sɜːrdʒ]', 'n.汹涌；波涛；猛增 v.汹涌；涌起；激增；[海]缆绳滑脱', '1. A surge of demonstrators broke through the fence. 汹涌而来的示威者冲破了围栏。 2. The great surge had built up in the Gulf Stream. 汹涌的巨浪在墨西哥湾流形成了。 3. Oil was the prime cause of the price surge. 石油是物价上涨的主要原因。 4. The tides surged over the rocks. 潮水奔腾着涌过礁石。', '过去式: surged 过去分词: surged 现在分词: surging 第三人称单数: surges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('symphony', '[\'sɪmfəni]', 'n.交响乐', '1. The first movement of the symphony is beautiful. 这部交响乐的第一乐章是很优美的。 2. I like listening to the symphony. 我喜欢听交响乐。', '名词复数: symphonies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('massive', '[\'mæsɪv]', 'adj.巨大的；大量的；大规模的；大范围的；严重的', '1. A massive boulder blocked the entrance of the cave. 一块巨大的圆石堵住了山洞的入口。 2. We have seen massive changes in recent years. 这几年我们经历了巨大的变化。 3. The soldier suffered a massive haemorrhage and died soon after. 那个战士经受了大量出血的痛苦，不久便去世了。 4. We must make massive efforts to improve things. 我们必须作出极大的努力去改善一切。', '副词: massively 名词: massiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inflict', '[ɪn\'flɪkt]', 'vt.使遭受；施以；加害；折磨', '1. We inflicted a crushing defeat on the enemy. 我们把敌军打得一败涂地。 2. We should inflict severe chastisement on criminals. 我们应该对罪犯施加严厉的惩罚。 3. Don\'t inflict your belief on me. 不要把你的想法强加于我。 4. Don\'t inflict damage on any person. 不要伤害任何人。', '形容词: inflictive 名词: inflicter 过去式: inflicted 过去分词: inflicted 现在分词: inflicting 第三人称单数: inflicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elicit', '[i\'lɪsɪt]', 'vt.引出；诱出；探出', '1. The detectives tried to elicit where he had hidden his loot. 侦探试图诱使他说出他藏匿赃物的地方。 2. I could elicit no response from him. 我从他那里套不出任何反应。 3. At last we have elicited the truth from him. 我们终于从他那里探得真相。 4. He succeeded in eliciting the information he needed from her. 他从她那里问出了他所需要的信息。', '名词: elicitation 过去式: elicited 过去分词: elicited 现在分词: eliciting 第三人称单数: elicits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extinction', '[ɪk\'stɪŋkʃn]', 'n.消失；消减；废止', '1. Its extinction is just a question of time. 它的消失只是一个时间问题。 2. The World Dinosaur Valley brings back from extinction the most mammoth creatures our planet has ever known. 恐龙世界将呈现出世界上最多的已然消失的猛犸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('device', '[dɪ\'vaɪs]', 'n.装置；设备；策略；设计', '1. The data logger device has been fitted to ship\'s engine room. 数字记录仪装置已安装在船只的机舱里。 2. The printer is the most commonly used output device after the monitor. 打印机是除显示器外最常用的输出设备。 3. It\'s just a tactical device to get over a split in their own Party. 这不过是他的想要克服党内分歧的一种策略。 4. Sending advertising by mail is very successful as a marketing device. 邮寄广告作为一种营销策略是非常成功的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assign', '[ə\'saɪn]', 'vt.分配；指定；指派；归因；确定 n.受让人', '1. All the students are assigned to suitable jobs. 所有的学生都分到了合适的工作。 2. For example, you might assign each order a unique order number. 例如,可能会为每个订单分配一个唯一的订单号。 3. After establishing roles, you can assign individual users to a role. 建立角色后,可以将各个用户分配到角色。 4. For each class, you have to assign an instance name. 对于每个类,您都必须指定一个实例名称。', '形容词: assignable 副词: assignably 名词: assignability 过去式: assigned 过去分词: assigned 现在分词: assigning 第三人称单数: assigns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shroud', '[ʃraʊd]', 'n.寿衣；裹尸布；覆盖物 v.用某物覆盖或遮蔽某物', '1. There are no pockets in a shroud. 寿衣没有口袋。 2. With my thread and needle, I’ll make the shroud. 用我的针和线，我将为他做寿衣。 3. The doctor wanted us to use the sheet for a shroud. 医生想让我们用床单当裹尸布。 4. A shroud of secrecy surrounds the plan. 这个计划神秘莫测。 5. The whole jail was shrouded in darkness. 整座监狱笼罩在黑暗之中。', '过去式: shrouded 过去分词: shrouded 现在分词: shrouding 第三人称单数: shrouds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confederate', '[kən\'fedərət]', 'n.同盟者；同盟国；同伙 Confederate：美国南部联盟. adj.同盟的；联合的 v.（使)结盟；（使)联合', '1. The thief was arrested, but his confederate escaped. 小偷被逮住了，但他的同伙却逃之夭夭。 2. Confederate forces defeated in Federal army in both battles. 同盟国势力打败了两次战役中的联邦军队。 3. The country tried to confederate with other countries for mutual safety. 这个国家为了共同安全，曾试图与别的国家结盟。', '形容词: confederative 过去式: confederated 过去分词: confederated 现在分词: confederating 第三人称单数: confederates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('serious', '[\'sɪriəs]', 'adj.严肃的；严重的；认真的；危急的；庄重的', '1. Do not treat this serious matter as a joke. 不要把这件严肃的事情当作笑料。 2. A serious look passed over his face. 他脸上显出一副严肃的神色。 3. There was a serious motor smash on the bridge. 桥上发生了严重的汽车相撞事故。 4. We are today facing a serious credit crunch. 我们今日正面对严重的信贷困难。', '副词: seriously 名词: seriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('critical', '[\'krɪtɪkl]', 'adj.批评的；挑剔的；决定性的；危险的 adj.临界的', '1. It is difficult enough to be critical of our own mistakes. 对我们自己的错误采取批评的态度确实非常困难。 2. She viewed the findings with a critical eye. 她以批评的眼光看待这些研究结果。 3. Our clients are very critical on quality. 我们的客户对商品的质量是很挑剔的。 4. Joint strategic maneuver is critical. 联合战略行动是决定性的。 5. These materials become quite soft and flexible above critical temperature. 这些材料在临界温度以上变得十分柔软和易于弯曲。', '副词: critically 名词: criticalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chaste', '[tʃeɪst]', 'adj.贞洁的；纯洁的；朴素的', '1. A wife loyal to her husband is chaste. 一个忠于丈夫的妻子是贞洁的。 2. These girls are told by the nuns to be chaste. 修女们教这些女孩子要贞洁。 3. She gave him a chaste kiss on the cheek. 她在他的脸颊上留下了纯洁的一吻。 4. She wore a chaste gold chain around her neck. 她戴着一条造型简洁的金项链。', '副词: chastely 比较级: chaster 最高级: chastest 名词: chasteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gregarious', '[ɡrɪ\'ɡeriəs]', 'adj.爱社交的；群居的', '1. She\'s very outgoing and gregarious. 她非常外向，喜欢交际。 2. Gregarious website is changing the life of people with rapid rate. 社交网站正在以飞快的速度改变着人们的生活。 3. These animals are highly gregarious. 这些动物非常喜欢群居。', '副词: gregariously 名词: gregariousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('balk', '[bɔːk]', 'v.阻止；突然停止；退缩；拒绝 n.障碍；错误；失败 n.梁木 [棒球]佯投； 犯规动作； [游戏]开球区.', '1. Professor Xu Benli, of the Shanghai University of Sport, says successful sportspeople should not balk at turning over half of their earnings. 上海体育学院徐本力教授表示，功成名就的运动员不应拒绝上缴一半的收入。 2. The high price is a balk to me. 对我来说，价格太高是一个障碍。 3. There are small holes in the balk of a field, where crabs and fish accumulate in the rainy season. 田间的梁木上有小洞口，螃蟹和鱼在雨季的时候会聚集在里面。 4. A player with ball in hand must play from the balk. 拿球的选手必须从开球区开始打。', '名词: balker');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reddish', '[\'redɪʃ]', 'adj.略带红色的；微红的', '1. Light reddish grey clothes suit him. 他适合穿葡萄灰色的衣服。 2. She brought a coat with reddish fur. 她买了一件略带红色皮毛的衣服。 3. The woman busily collected the ripened reddish berries. 那妇女忙著采集成熟的淡红色的莓果。 4. We recognized the robin by its reddish underparts. 我们通过其微红色的下部认识知更鸟', '名词: reddishness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cliff', '[klɪf]', 'n.悬崖；峭壁', '1. The sea had undermined the cliff. 海水侵蚀了悬崖的基部。 2. He couldn\'t find a hold on the cliff. 他在悬崖上找不到一个可以站住脚的地方。 3. The narrow path zigzags up the cliff. 这条狭窄的小径曲曲折折地向峭壁伸延。 4. They slowly clawed their way up the cliff. 他们缓慢地爬上峭壁。', '形容词: cliffy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pollutant', '[pə\'luːtənt]', 'n.污染物质', '1. The strategy specifies the maximum concentration of a pollutant which is allowed to be emitted. 这个策略确定了一种允许排放的污染物质的最高浓度。 2. Over time, the Norwegians have expanded their accounts to include data on air pollutant emissions. 随着时间的过去，挪威人已经扩大他们的帐户包括在空气污染物质发射上的数据。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('weird', '[wɪrd]', 'adj.离奇的；古怪的；怪异的 n.命运；预言者', '1. He looks like nothing on earth in those weird clothes. 他穿著奇装异服难看极了。 2. Jane, I found that guy somewhat weird. 珍妮, 我发觉那家伙有点古怪。 3. That was really a weird movie. 那部电影真怪异! 4. I heard weird shrieks in the darkness. 我在黑暗中听到奇怪的尖叫声。', '副词: weirdly 比较级: weirder 最高级: weirdest 名词: weirdness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dominant', '[\'dɑːmɪnənt]', 'adj.主要的；占优势的；显性的 n.主宰者；显性基因', '1. Peace was the dominant theme of the conference. 和平是大会的首要议题。 2. He is a dominant leader in our university. 他是我们学校最主要的一位领导。 3. The right hand is dominant in most people. 大多数人的右手是优势手。 4. The company can\'t preserve its dominant position in the market. 该公司在市场上不能让自己保持优势地位。 5. We should be the dominant of ourselves. 我们要做自己的主宰者。', '副词: dominantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('restricted', '[rɪ\'strɪktɪd]', 'adj.受限制的；有限的；保密的 动词restrict的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The drug has only a restricted commercial use. 这种麻醉药用作商品是极受限制的。 2. He managed to twist himself round in the restricted space. 他设法在有限的空间内转过身来。 3. He leads a very restricted life. 他的生活面非常狭窄。 4. Don\'t show this restricted material to others. 不要把这些内部参考资料给别人看。', '副词: restrictedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vulnerable', '[\'vʌlnərəbl]', 'adj.易受伤害的；有弱点的；脆弱的', '1. Achilles was vulnerable only in his heel. 阿基里斯只有脚后跟会受伤害。 2. The potato is vulnerable to several pests. 马铃薯易受几种害虫的侵害。 3. Young birds are very vulnerable to predators. 幼小的鸟易受食肉动物伤害。 4. Satellites are as vulnerable as they are valuable. 卫星价值很大但也很脆弱。', '副词: vulnerably 名词: vulnerability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insert', '[ɪn\'sɜːrt]', 'v.插入；嵌入 n.插入物', '1. She inserted the key into the lock. 她把钥匙插入锁中。 2. You can insert additional pages into that book. 你可以把附加的散页插入那本书里。 3. The next procedure is to insert the battery. 接下来的步骤是装进电池。 4. He tried to insert an advertisement in a newspaper. 他设法将广告刊登在报纸上。 5. She found an insert in the book. 她在那本书中找到了一个插入物。', '名词: inserter 过去式: inserted 过去分词: inserted 现在分词: inserting 第三人称单数: inserts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compare', '[kəm\'per]', 'v.比较；对比；比喻 n.比较；对照', '1. I compared the copy with the original, but there was not much difference. 我比较了复印件和原件，但是差别不是很大。 2. The police compared the suspect\'s fingerprints with those found at the crime scene. 警察将嫌疑犯的指纹和犯罪现场的指纹进行了对比。 3. Life is poetically compared to the morning dew. 在诗歌中，人生被比喻为朝露。 4. She is lovely beyond compare. 她真是可爱得无与伦比。', '名词: comparer 过去式: compared 过去分词: compared 现在分词: comparing 第三人称单数: compares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('optimum', '[\'ɑːptɪməm]', 'adj.最佳的；最适宜的 n.最适宜', '1. The market offers optimum condition for sale. 市场为销售提供了最佳条件。 2. You have established the optimum price. 你已制定了最佳价格。 3. The optimum starting age is ten. 最佳起始年龄是10岁。 4. Now your advice is very optimum. 现在你的建议是很适宜的。 5. Strive for optimum, not maximum, performance. 不求最多、最花哨，只求最适宜。', '名词复数: optima');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flighty', '[\'flaɪti]', 'adj.轻浮的；不负责任的；反复无常的', '1. He said I was too flighty to be a good supervisor. 他说我太轻浮不能成为一名好的管理员。 2. She is too flighty to take care of young children. 她太不负责任, 不能照顾小孩。', '副词: flightily 比较级: flightier 最高级: flightiest 名词: flightiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sunset', '[\'sʌnset]', 'n.日落；衰落时期（尤指人的晚年）', '1. It is seen in the sky after sunset. 日落後可在天空中看到它。 2. By sunset we had covered thirty miles. 到日落的时候，我们已走了三十英里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clause', '[klɔːz]', 'n.条款；[语]从句', '1. There is a contentious clause in the treaty. 这条约中有一条有争议的条款。 2. A penalty clause was written into the contract. 在合同中写入了一项罚款条款。 3. Please pay attention to this clause in the sentence. 请注意看句中的这个从句。 4. This is an attributive clause. 这是一个定语从句。', '形容词: clausal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exhaustive', '[ɪɡ\'zɔːstɪv]', 'adj.彻底的；详尽的；消耗的', '1. He has made an exhaustive study of the problem. 他对这个问题进行了彻底的研究。 2. After an exhaustive search the missing document was found. 经过彻底搜寻丢失的文件被找到了。 3. An exhaustive investigation of the facts proves the contrary. 彻底地调查事实后发现情况正好相反。 4. To compile an exhaustive dictionary is an exhausting task. 编写一本详尽的字典是一件吃力的工作。', '副词: exhaustively 名词: exhaustiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('continuity', '[ˌkɑːntə\'nuːəti]', 'n.连续性', '1. There is no continuity between the two paragraphs. 那两段间无连续性。 2. Mr Keller sees continuity where others see helter-skelter change. 别人眼中杂乱无章的变迁在凯勒眼里却具有连续性。', '名词复数: continuities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bent', '[bent]', 'bend的过去式和过去分词. adj.下定决心的；弯曲的 n.嗜好', '1. The branches bent in the wind. 树枝被风吹弯了。 2. Judy bent her face low over the notebook. 朱迪把脸凑近笔记本。 3. The branch bent but didn\'t break when the boy climbed along it. 那男孩爬上树枝时，树枝弯曲了，但是没有折断。 4. He\'s bent on completing his essay. 他决心要写完他的随笔。 5. He has a bent for art. 他生性爱好艺术。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('juvenile', '[\'dʒuːvənl]', 'adj.青少年的；幼稚的 n.青少年；青少年读物；幼雏；扮演少年的演员', '1. I\'m afraid he\'ll ultimately become a juvenile delinquent. 我恐怕他最终会成为一名青少年罪犯。 2. They are holding a forum on juvenile delinquency. 他们正举行一个有关青少年犯罪的讨论会。 3. He is an expert in juvenile delinquency. 他是研究青少年犯罪的专家。 4. He wrote down to the juvenile readers. 他为青少年读者写浅显的作品。 5. They are holding a forum on juvenile delinquency. 他们正举行一个有关青少年犯罪的讨论会。', '副词: juvenilely 名词: juvenileness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spout', '[spaʊt]', 'n.【C】喷口；水管；水柱 v.喷出；滔滔不绝地说', '1. The spout of the teapot is jammed by tea. 茶壶的壶口被茶叶堵住了。 2. A thin cloud of steam was rising from the spout . 喷口处冒出一股薄薄的水蒸气。 3. The eensy weensy spider went up the water spout. 小蜘蛛顺着水管向上爬， 4. Rain runs down a spout from our roof to the ground. 雨水经过雨水管从我们的屋顶流到了地上。 5. Water is spouting out of the pipe. 水正从管子里喷出来。', '名词: spouter 过去式: spouted 过去分词: spouted 现在分词: spouting 第三人称单数: spouts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reflection', '[rɪ\'flekʃn]', 'n.倒影；反射；反映；沉思；考虑', '1. The cat felt curious when she saw her own reflection in the mirror. 小猫看到自己在镜子中的倒影，感到很好奇。 2. The moon is bright only by reflection. 月亮靠反射发光。 3. They were studying the reflection of sound waves. 他们在研究声波的反射。 4. His dark looks are a reflection of his unhappiness. 他阴郁的神情是内心苦恼的反映。', '形容词: reflectional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confer', '[kən\'fɜːr]', 'v.商讨；授予，赐予', '1. I must confer with my lawyer before I decide. 我必须先同我的律师商量一下才能做出决定。 2. I will confer with him on the subject. 我将和他商议这件事。 3. The Queen conferred knighthood on several distinguished men. 女王将爵士头衔授予几位杰出人士。 4. The university confers master degree on her. 学校授予她硕士学位。', '形容词: conferrable 名词: conferment 过去式: conferred 过去分词: conferred 现在分词: conferring 第三人称单数: confers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('replenish', '[rɪ\'plenɪʃ]', 'vt.补充；再装满 vi.补充', '1. We need to replenish our stocks of coal. 我们需要再次补充煤的储备。 2. It\'s time to replenish the shop with the news year\'s goods. 该为这家商店补充新年货物了。 3. These foods replenish the skeletal needs of the body. 这些食物补充身体骨骼的需要。 4. Perhaps to replenish their energies for the coming week. 可能是为新的一个星期的到来而补充能量。 5. We need to replenish our stocks of coal. 我们需要再次补充煤的储备。', '名词: replenisher 过去式: replenished 过去分词: replenished 现在分词: replenishing 第三人称单数: replenishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('viral', '[\'vaɪrəl]', 'adj.病毒的 n.病毒式传播；【经】病毒式营销', '1. A viral illness left her barely able to walk. 一场病毒引起的疾病使她走路都十分困难。 2. Mumps is an acute contagious viral infection. 流行性腮腺炎是一种急性接触性病毒传染 3. Animals may serve as a vehicle for viral transmission. 动物可能成为病毒传播的媒介。 4. Some viral diseases are more severe during pregnancy. 有些病毒病在妊娠期间比较严重。', '副词: virally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refined', '[rɪ\'faɪnd]', 'adj.精炼的；优雅的；精细的 动词refine的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The oil will be refined. 这些石油将被精炼。 2. He has a refined palate. 他精于品味。 3. She\'s so refined that she always eats cake with a little fork. 她非常文雅，吃蛋糕一定用小叉子。 4. He is a man of subtle and refined sensibility. 他是个感情细腻的男子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arrogant', '[\'ærəɡənt]', 'adj.傲慢的；自大的', '1. One should never be arrogant even when he is at his best. 一个人在最得意时也不应傲慢。 2. Well as he does in study, he is not arrogant. 虽然他功课很好，却一点都不傲慢。 3. It\'s arrogant of you to say that. 你竟然那样说，未免太自大了。 4. He is an arrogant man. 他是一个自高自大的人。', '副词: arrogantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ferret', '[\'ferɪt]', 'n.白鼬；雪貂 v.用雪貂打猎；搜出', '1. Whatever plans they had for the ferret and himself had now been abandoned. 但他打算让白鼬做的事以及他自己的计划全都泡汤了。 2. Ferret and cats both like to chase furry stuff. 雪貂的个性和猫一样喜欢追逐毛茸茸的东西。 3. The detective ferret out the criminal. 那位侦探把犯人搜出来了。 4. See if you can ferret out any information about his past that we can use to discredit him. 看看你能否查获我们可以用来使他名誉扫地的历史记录。', '形容词: ferrety 名词: ferreter 过去式: ferreted 过去分词: ferreted 现在分词: ferreting 第三人称单数: ferrets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('differentiate', '[ˌdɪfə\'renʃieɪt]', 'vt.区分；使差异；求导数 vi.区别；产生差别；区别对待', '1. Can you differentiate one variety from the other? 你能将这两个品种区别开来吗? 2. He cannot differentiate the two flowers. 他无法辨认这两种花。 3. The only way to differentiate yourself from the competition is through service. 只有服务才能真正使你在竞争中凸显。 4. I cannot differentiate between these two things. 我无法区别这两个东西。', '名词: differentiation 过去式: differentiated 过去分词: differentiated 现在分词: differentiating 第三人称单数: differentiates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fund', '[fʌnd]', 'n.基金 vt.资助；转为（长期贷款）', '1. Our company is in want of fund. 我们的公司需要资金。 2. The pension fund owns shares in several major public companies. 该养老基金在几家主要出售股份给公众的公司中均有股份。 3. The factory has built up reserve fund. 这个工厂已积累了后备基金。 4. A fund will be set up for the dead men\'s families. 抚恤死难工人家属的基金会即将建立起来。 5. The National Asthma Campaign is funding research into allergy and air pollution. 国家哮喘运动组织为对过敏和空气污染进行研究提供基金。', '过去式: funded 过去分词: funded 现在分词: funding 第三人称单数: funds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tolerable', '[\'tɑːlərəbl]', 'adj.还不错的；可容忍的', '1. We had a very tolerable lunch. 我们吃了顿很不错的午餐。 2. She inspected the rooms and found them perfectly tolerable. 她仔细看了房间，觉得都很不错。 3. Your blunders are not tolerable. 你的过失是不可容忍的。 4. The doctors manage to keep the pain at a tolerable level. 医生设法让疼痛保持在一个可以承受的程度。', '副词: tolerably 名词: tolerability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('routine', '[ruː\'tiːn]', 'n.例行公事；常规；无聊 adj.常规的；例行的；乏味的', '1. We must introduce some system into our office routine. 我们须在我们日常公务中建立一些制度。 2. They did it as a matter of routine. 他们那样做只是例行公事。 3. This type of work rapidly becomes routine. 这种工作很快就变得乏味无聊。 4. You just need to break out of that boring routine. 你只需改变一成不变的无聊生活。 5. The film is a love story, with routine portraits of a conductor and a violinist. 那部电影是一个爱情故事,对於乐队指挥和小提琴手之间的爱情描写都是老一套。', '副词: routinely 名词: routinism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('initial', '[ɪ\'nɪʃl]', 'n.(词)首字母 adj.开始的；最初的；字首的 vt.签姓名的首字母于', '1. This is a letter paper personalized with his initials. 这是一张有他姓名首字母的信纸。 2. After the initial cheers,the noise of the crowd began to die away as the group started playing. 开始的欢呼声结束以后，乐队开始演奏，人们的喧闹声也随之逐渐消失。 3. We are through the initial testing period. 我们通过了最初的考试阶段 4. The word “hour” is pronounced without an initial aspirate. hour一词的首字母h不发送气音。 5. She initialed a handkerchief and gave it to that young man. 她在手帕上绣上姓名的首字母，把它送给了那个年轻人。', '副词: initially 名词: initialness 过去式: initialed/initialled 过去分词: initialed/initialled 现在分词: initialing/initialling 第三人称单数: initials/initials');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('press', '[pres]', 'v.按；压；逼迫；强迫服役；征用 n.新闻界；出版社；报刊；新闻舆论；压；熨烫机；印刷机', '1. Please press the controller to turn the machine on. 请按控制器来开机。 2. Press this button in case of fire. 遇火灾时按下此钮。 3. The book is crumpled and needs press. 书皱了需要压一压。 4. Press firmly on the wound to stop the bleeding. 用力压住伤口止血。 5. He denied that he had leaked the news to the press. 他否认曾将这则消息泄漏给新闻界。', '过去式: pressed 过去分词: pressed 现在分词: pressing 第三人称单数: presses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insult', '[ɪn\'sʌlt]', 'n.侮辱；辱骂；冒犯 vt.侮辱；辱骂；凌辱', '1. He made a witty comeback to the insult. 他对别人的侮辱给予一个机智的反驳。 2. She reacted to the insult by turning her back on him. 她受辱之后就不再理睬他了。 3. He shouted insults at the boy who had kicked him. 他大声辱骂那个踢了他的男孩。 4. He felt deeply insulted by her rude words. 她无礼的言词使他深感受辱。', '副词: insultingly 名词: insulter 过去式: insulted 过去分词: insulted 现在分词: insulting 第三人称单数: insults');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deliberate', '[dɪ\'lɪbərət]', 'adj.深思熟虑的；故意的；从容不迫的 v.仔细考虑；研讨', '1. She has a slow, deliberate way of talking. 她谈话的方式缓慢而审慎. 2. He told us a deliberate lie. 他存心说谎。 3. It had more the appearance of a deliberate crime than an accident. 那很像是蓄意的罪行，而不像是意外的事故。 4. He entered the room with deliberate steps. 他从容不迫地走进室内。 5. We had no time to deliberate on the problem. 我们没有时间仔细思考这个问题.', '副词: deliberately 名词: deliberateness 过去式: deliberated 过去分词: deliberated 现在分词: deliberating 第三人称单数: deliberates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subsequent', '[\'sʌbsɪkwənt]', 'adj.随后的；后来的', '1. Subsequent events proved me wrong. 後来发生的事证明我错了。 2. He confessed to other crimes subsequent to the bank robbery. 他供认抢劫银行案後，又坦白了其他罪行。 3. Subsequent to its success as a play, it was made into a film. 该剧在舞台上获得成功之後，又摄制成了电影。 4. Subsequent events confirmed our doubts. 后来发生的事证实了我们的怀疑。', '副词: subsequently 名词: subsequence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cardinal', '[\'kɑːrdɪnl]', 'n.红衣主教；鲜红色；基数；北美红雀 adj.主要的；深红色的', '1. I\'ve had dinner with Bill and Cardinal Spellman. 我同比尔和斯佩尔曼红衣主教一起吃过晚饭。 2. The cardinal includes 1, 2, 3, etc. 基数词包括1、2、3等等。 3. A cardinal perched momently on the dogwood branch. 一只北美红雀在山茱萸上停留了片刻。 4. Every one suspects himself of at least one of the cardinal virtues. 每个人都认为他自己至少有一种主要的品德。', '名词: cardinalship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adhesive', '[əd\'hiːsɪv]', 'adj.有粘性的；难忘的 n.粘着剂', '1. He also invented the adhesive postage stamp. 他还发明了粘性邮票。 2. The adhesive will stick to most clean surfaces. 粘胶剂会粘在非常清洁的表面。 3. You need a strong adhesive to bond wood to metal. 需要强力胶才能把木料粘在金属上。', '副词: adhesively 名词: adhesiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perceive', '[pər\'sːv]', 'v.注意到；觉察到；认为；理解', '1. I plainly perceive some objections remain. 我清楚地察觉到还有一些反对意见。 2. We can perceive his sorrow by the looks on his face. 我们从他的表情中觉察出悲伤。 3. Indeed, this problem is greater than one may perceive. 确实，这个问题远大于你所能感知到的。 4. They perceive television as entertainment. 他们将电视视为娱乐。', '形容词: perceivable 副词: perceivably 名词: perceiver 过去式: perceived 过去分词: perceived 现在分词: perceiving 第三人称单数: perceives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dodge', '[dɑːdʒ]', 'v.避开；躲避 n.躲避；诡计', '1. He dodged past me. 他躲躲闪闪地从我旁边走过。 2. He dodged the falling rock and escaped unhurt. 他闪身躲过了滚落的岩石，安然脱险了。 3. She was sharp-witted enough to dodge her attacker. 她才思敏捷足以避开别人的攻击。 4. The man jumped aside to dodge the speeding truck. 这人跳到旁边以躲避疾驶的卡车。 5. Do you like to go playing dodge ball with us? 要不要和我们一起去打躲避球?', '过去式: dodged 过去分词: dodged 现在分词: dodging 第三人称单数: dodges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decent', '[\'diːsnt]', 'adj.相当好的；体面的；适当的；正派的', '1. Are there any decent restaurants around here? 这附近有没有好的餐厅？ 2. He dreamed of living in decent conditions. 他梦想着过体面的生活。 3. The lack of decent public transport is a great disadvantage. 没有适当的公共交通工具是很不方便的。 4. John and his wife Leah are very decent people. 约翰是他的妻子丽亚都是非常正派的人。', '副词: decently 名词: decentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('helpless', '[\'helpləs]', 'adj.无助的；无依靠的', '1. Girls just love helpless animals. 女孩子就是喜欢无助的动物。 2. In other words, they make him feel less helpless in the face of adversity. 换句话说，他们让他在面对逆境时不再感到那么无助。 3. They are helpless, drifting wherever the currents and tides take them. 他们无所依凭，随波逐流。 4. Fate was kind to the helpless baby. 这个无依无靠的婴儿命里注定不该死。', '副词: helplessly 名词: helplessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tedium', '[\'tiːdiəm]', 'n.单调乏味；沉闷', '1. He has got used to the tedium of life here. 他已经习惯了这里单调的生活。 2. I didn\'t know how to while away my tedium. 我不知道如何度过乏味的时刻。 3. Risk is what separates the good part of life from the tedium. 风险把生活中的精彩篇章与单调无聊区分开。 4. We played games to relieve the tedium of the journey. 我们玩游戏,来解除旅行的沉闷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adverse', '[\'ædvɜːrs]', 'adj.不利的；逆向的；有害的', '1. The judge gave us an adverse decision. 法官作出对我们不利的判决。 2. He ignored all kinds of adverse comments about him. 他不理睬各种各样对他不利的评论。 3. The development was adverse to our interests. 这种发展与我们的利益背道而驰。 4. Diseases are adverse to the best growth of children. 疾病对儿童的健康成长是有害的。', '副词: adversely 名词: adverseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distract', '[dɪ\'strækt]', 'vt.分散；转移；分心；困扰', '1. The film managed to distract me from these problems for a while. 这部影片分散了我的注意力，让我暂时忘记了这些难题。 2. It was all a ploy to distract attention from his real aims. 那纯粹是障眼法，用以分散人们对他真正意图的注意力。 3. We must change our route to distract the attention of the enemy. 我们必须改变行军路线以转移敌人的注意力。 4. Once she gets involved in a research, nothing can distract her mind from it. 她一旦潜心钻研某一课题,任何事情都无法使她分心。', '形容词: distractive 副词: distractingly 过去式: distracted 过去分词: distracted 现在分词: distracting 第三人称单数: distracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('culpable', '[\'kʌlpəbl]', 'adj.该责备的；有罪的', '1. THe man who killed children is culpable. 杀害小孩的人应该受谴责。 2. I can not be held culpable for their mistakes. 不能把他们的错误归咎于我。 3. The judge found the man culpable. 法官认为那个人有罪。', '副词: culpably 名词: culpability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intelligent', '[ɪn\'telɪdʒənt]', 'adj.聪明的；智能的', '1. Though very intelligent, she is nevertheless rather modest. 她很聪明，倒也很谦虚。 2. The student gave an intelligent answer. 这个学生给出了一个聪明的回答。 3. Maybe the earth has been visited by intelligent creatures from outer space. 也许太空的智慧生物已经访问过地球。', '形容词: intelligential 副词: intelligently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adequate', '[\'ædɪkwət]', 'adj.足够的；适当的；能胜任的', '1. We had adequate food for a week\'s journey. 我们有足够的食物可以做一星期的旅行。 2. He sought for an adequate solution to the problem. 他寻求解决这个问题的适当办法。 3. I hope he will be adequate to the job. 我希望他将胜任这一工作。', '副词: adequately 名词: adequacy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fraught', '[frɔːt]', 'adj.充满的；伴随的；忧伤的；忧虑的', '1. The journey was fraught with difficulties. 旅途充满艰辛。 2. The expedition into the jungle was fraught with danger. 到原始森林去探险充满了危险。 3. There\'s no need to look so fraught! 用不着那么愁眉苦脸的。 4. Next week will be particularly fraught as we\'ve just lost our secretary. 我们的秘书刚刚辞职,下星期特别令人担心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('injurious', '[ɪn\'dʒʊrəriəs]', 'adj.有害的；中伤的', '1. Smoking is injurious to health. 吸烟对健康有害。 2. All sediment deposition is not injurious . 并不是所有的泥沙淤积都是有害的。 3. His behavior is injurious to the interests of the vast majority of people. 他的行为有损于大多数人民的利益。', '副词: injuriously 名词: injuriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('torturous', '[\'tɔːtʃərəs]', 'adj.折磨的；痛苦的', '1. Each member of their pod experiences such torturous deaths as they are holographically interconnected in energy flow. 每一圆荚中的成员均体验如此受折磨的死亡，因为他们在能量流中是全息互联的。 2. After 3 years of torturous imprisonment, he was finally set free. 经过了三年痛苦的坐牢，他终于被放出来了。 3. Mind control drugs and experiments were torturous to the victims. 精神控制药物及实验对受害者来说是痛苦的。', '副词: torturously');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alliance', '[ə\'laɪəns]', 'n.联盟；联姻；结盟 Alliance [地理名词].', '1. They broke up the alliance. 他们中止了联盟。 2. The alliance has been forged in the crucible of war. 这个联盟经受了战争的严峻考验。 3. Gerard required a different alliance to aid his career. 则杰拉就需要一个不同的联姻来帮助他的事业。 4. The two countries made an alliance. 两国结盟。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('factual', '[\'fæktʃuəl]', 'adj.事实的；真实的', '1. The jury was convinced of the factual testimony. 陪审团相信了这充满事实的证词。 2. They couched criticisms in factual language. 他们用事实的语言表达了批评。 3. This seems to be slanted against us from getting factual data. 这不利于我们获得真实的数据。 4. He has difficulty distinguishing between imaginary and factual information. 他难以区分假想的和真实的信息。', '副词: factually 名词: factuality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('regular', '[\'reɡjələr]', 'adj.有规律的；定期的；经常的；正规的；整齐的；规则的', '1. He made a regular visit to his parents. 他定期看望父母亲。 2. We will remain in regular contact with them. 我们将和他们保持经常的联系。 3. Please act according to the regular procedure. 请按照正规的程序行事。 4. He is a handsome young man with regular features. 他是个五官端正的英俊青年。', '副词: regularly 名词: regularity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('moist', '[mɔɪst]', 'adj.潮湿的；湿润的；[医]湿性的', '1. This gave a warm and moist feeling to the picture. 这样让整张画有了些温暖和潮湿的感觉。 2. Winds from the sea are usually moist. 海风通常是潮湿的。 3. There is a moist wind from the sea. 海上吹来了一阵湿润的风。 4. The story was so sad that at the end my eyes were moist with tears. 故事非常让人伤心,最后我的眼睛湿润了。', '副词: moistly 比较级: moister 最高级: moistest 名词: moistness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('submerge', '[səb\'mɜːrdʒ]', 'vt.使浸没；潜入水中；覆盖 vi.浸没', '1. I watched the submarine submerge. 我望着潜艇潜入水中。', '名词: submergence 过去式: submerged 过去分词: submerged 现在分词: submerging 第三人称单数: submerges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('renaissance', '[\'renəsɑːns]', 'n.文艺复兴；再生', '1. Her book captures the quintessence of Renaissance humanism. 她的书抓住了文艺复兴时期人文主义的精髓。 2. Florence is the shrine of the Renaissance. 佛罗伦萨是文艺复兴的圣地。 3. These are the cultural legacies of the Renaissance. 这些是文艺复兴时期的文化遗产。 4. Leonardo da Vinci is a famous artist in the Italian Renaissance. 利奥纳多·达·芬奇是意大利文艺复兴时期的一位知名画家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prune', '[pruːn]', 'v.修剪；削减 n.梅干；洋李脯', '1. You should prune your roses in the spring. 你应该在春天修剪一下你的玫瑰花。 2. It is our job to prune the side branches of these trees. 我们的工作就是修剪这些树的侧枝。 3. The gardener pruned the dead branches. 园丁剪去枯枝。 4. Next year\'s budget will have to be drastically pruned. 下一年度的预算将大幅度削减。', '名词: pruner 过去式: pruned 过去分词: pruned 现在分词: pruning 第三人称单数: prunes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frost', '[frɔːst]', 'n.霜；霜冻；严寒 v.结霜；冻死；用糖衣装饰', '1. The windscreen was covered with frost. 挡风玻璃上结了霜。 2. Sweet potatoes decayed after the frost. 霜下了之后,地瓜烂掉了。 3. The crops were blasted by frost. 农作物被霜冻毁了。 4. Frost caused the split in the rock. 霜冻使岩石裂了一条缝。 5. The cold has frosted the windows. 寒冷的天气使窗子上结满了霜。', '过去式: frosted 过去分词: frosted 现在分词: frosting 第三人称单数: frosts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plausible', '[\'plɔːzəbl]', 'adj.似真实合理的；动听的；看起来有道理的，貌似可信的', '1. Such a theory seems very plausible. 这一理论貌似十分有理。 2. He can not find a plausible reason for his absence. 翻译他找不到缺席的合理理由。 3. Though controversial, it is plausible. 虽有争议，却似乎行得通。 4. He trotted out a most plausible story, but most of us were inclined to doubt the truth of it. 他提出了一个听起来很有道理的说法，但我们大多数人对此都持怀疑态度。', '副词: plausibly 名词: plausibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('submit', '[səb\'mɪt]', 'vt.使服从；使屈服；提交；递交；认为 vi.屈从', '1. We will submit ourselves to the court\'s judgement. 我们服从法庭的判决。 2. We have to submit ourselves to discipline. 我们必须遵守纪律。 3. He submitted his proposal for urban development to the city council. 他将城市发展建议提交市议会。 4. Please fill in and submit the form below. 请填写并递交以下表格。 5. They refused to submit to the unjust decision. 他们拒绝服从这个不公正的决定。', '名词: submittal 过去式: submitted 过去分词: submitted 现在分词: submitting 第三人称单数: submits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unshaken', '[ˌʌn\'ʃeɪkən]', 'adj.坚定的；不动摇的；泰然自若的', '1. They remain unshaken in their loyalty. 他们仍然忠贞不渝。 2. Do you have unshaken confidence in the Lord? 你对神的信仰坚定吗？ 3. Are you still unshaken in your integrity? 你还坚持你的耿直吗? 4. You-the unshaken trees; I am the leaf that quivers. 我是树叶震颤不停，你-一颗大树，永远坚定。（拟植物）', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sheer', '[ʃɪr]', 'adj.极轻薄的；陡峭的；全然的 adv.垂直地 v.避开；转向', '1. Chiffon is a fabric of sheer silk or rayon. 薄绸是一种极薄的丝绸或人造丝织物。 2. It\'s very difficult to climb a sheer cliff. 攀登陡峭的悬崖是很困难的。 3. She played a trick on him out of sheer devilment. 她捉弄他完全是为了寻开心。 4. He\'s so impatient that waiting in queues is sheer purgatory for him. 他毫无耐性，对他来说排队等候完全是活受罪。 5. The ground dropped away sheer at our feet. 我们脚下的地面垂直地陷落下去。 6. When he saw me coming he sheered off in the opposite direction. 他一看到我过来，掉头就走了。', '副词: sheerly 比较级: sheerer 最高级: sheerest 名词: sheerness 过去式: sheered 过去分词: sheered 现在分词: sheering 第三人称单数: sheers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yogurt', '[\'joʊɡərt]', 'n.酸奶；酵母乳 =yoghurt.', '1. Do you have any low- fat yogurt? 你要不要低脂的酸奶？ 2. Yogurt is without question one of the most nutritious foods on the planet. 优酪乳无疑地是地球上最富营养的食物之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ventilation', '[ˌventɪ\'leɪʃn]', 'n.通风；通风设备；充气；公开讨论', '1. This is a room with good ventilation. 这是个通风良好的房间。 2. Do not place the product in a separate enclosure unless proper ventilation are provided. 除非通风良好，不要把产品放在独立的封闭装置中。 3. I will close the ventilation, manholes and hatches until the firefighting team arrives. 应马上关闭离火源最近的通风设备、人孔等，等待消防人员的到来。 4. They altered the house to improve its ventilation. 他们把房子改装一下使它更通气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disinterested', '[dɪs\'ɪntrəstɪd]', 'adj.不感兴趣的；无私欲的；公平的；公正的 动词disinterest的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. But, the mere idea of having that much money is enough to make even the most disinterested students pay attention in a social studies class. 可是，哪怕仅仅是想到有这么一大笔钱，已经足够使那些对此最不感兴趣的学生也关注起这门社会学课程。 2. He is a disinterested person. 他是一个没有私心的人。 3. The God makes everyone disinterested. 上帝对每个人都是公平的！ 4. The judge gave a disinterested verdict. 法官作出了公正的判决', '副词: disinterestedly 名词: disinterestedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('profane', '[prə\'feɪn]', 'adj.亵渎的；不敬神的；世俗的 v.亵渎；玷污', '1. His profane language annoyed us. 他亵渎的言语激怒了我们。 2. I was sorry, I said, to hear them so very profane. 我说，我听见他们这样的蔑教，很难过。 3. They have profane the long uphold tradition of the church. 他们亵渎了教会长期沿袭的传统。 4. His action profaned the honour of his country. 他的行为玷污了国家的荣誉。', '形容词: profanatory 副词: profanely 名词: profaneness 过去式: profaned 过去分词: profaned 现在分词: profaning 第三人称单数: profanes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trot', '[trɑːt]', 'n.疾走；慢跑；老太婆；现成译本 （复数）trots:腹泻（与the连用）. v.小跑；快步走', '1. The old man set off at a quick trot. 老人快步走开了。 2. He had left me and broken into a trot towards his block. 他离开我突然朝他的街区疾走过去。 3. The horse started off at a steady trot. 那匹马快步稳健地跑了起来。 4. The horse trotted down the road. 马在路上小跑着。', '过去式: trotted 过去分词: trotted 现在分词: trotting 第三人称单数: trots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mandate', '[\'mændeɪt]', 'n.命令；指令；要求；授权 v.把(某一地区)置于委任管理下', '1. The government gave the police a mandate to reduce crime. 政府命令警方进一步打击犯罪活动。 2. We have a mandate from the union membership to proceed with strike action. 我们获得工会会员同意，继续罢工。 3. You should follow the doctor\'s mandate. 你该听从医师的要求。 4. Our election victory has given us a mandate to reform the economy. 我们在选举中获胜,这就使我们有权进行经济改革。 5. Britain was mandated to govern the former colony of German East Africa. 英国授权代管德国在东非的前殖民地。', '名词: mandator 过去式: mandated 过去分词: mandated 现在分词: mandating 第三人称单数: mandates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('languish', '[\'læŋɡwɪʃ]', 'v.衰弱无力；失去活力；受苦；憔悴', '1. Shares now languish around $13 per share. 股价现在衰弱到了每股%2413左右。 2. The housing market continues to languish. 房地产市场继续低迷。 3. My interest in music has languished slightly. 我对音乐的兴趣有点减退。 4. The flower languished from lack of water. 花因缺水而枯萎。', '副词: languishingly 名词: languisher 过去式: languished 过去分词: languished 现在分词: languishing 第三人称单数: languishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resent', '[rɪ\'zent]', 'vt.恨；生气', '1. Kate said she felt we resent her. 凯特说她感到我们大家恨她。 2. I resent the encroachment on my time. 我讨厌别人侵占我的时间。 3. I bitterly resent his attempts to interfere in my work. 我非常讨厌他企图干涉我的工作。 4. I resent having to get his permission for everything I do. 我讨厌做每件事都要得到他的许可。', '过去式: resented 过去分词: resented 现在分词: resenting 第三人称单数: resents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sewage', '[\'suːɪdʒ]', 'n.污水；污物', '1. The river was contaminated with sewage. 这河水被污水污染了。 2. The sewage pipes were choked with rubbish. 垃圾阻塞了污水管道。 3. The grave problem of public hygiene is connected with the inefficient sewage system of the city. 公共卫生方面的严重问题与该城低效率的污水处理系统有关。 4. Chemicals in the factory\'s sewage system have changed the ecology of the whole area. 这座工厂排出的化学物质改变了整个地区的生态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sample', '[\'sæmpl]', 'n.样品；样本 vt.采样；取样；品尝，体验', '1. Thousands of people have written in to us for a free sample. 现已有数千人给我们来信索要免费样品。 2. What I need is nothing but a sample. 我需要的不过是一件样品而已。 3. The sample size would have to be quadrupled. 样本量必须增大三倍。 4. I\'ll send you some sample menus. 我会给您寄些菜单样本去。 5. We sampled the stuff and found it satisfactory. 我们抽验了这批材料，认为满意。', '过去式: sampled 过去分词: sampled 现在分词: sampling 第三人称单数: samples');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indispensable', '[ˌɪndɪ\'spensəbl]', 'adj.不可缺少的', '1. The computer is now an indispensable tool in many businesses. 目前计算机是很多公司不可或缺的用具。 2. Air is indispensable to life. 空气是生命所必需的东西。 3. A good dictionary is indispensable for learning a foreign language. 学习外语离不开好的词典。 4. Air, food and water are indispensable to life. 空气，食物，水皆为生命不可缺者。', '副词: indispensably 名词: indispensability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slice', '[slaɪs]', 'n.薄片；部分；曲球 v.切成薄片；割；切开', '1. Please give me a slice of bread. 请给我一片面包。 2. This is just a slice of life. 这只是人生的一个片段罢了。 3. He also gets a slice of the profit. 他也得到一份利润。 4. A slice is a curving shot from left to right with severe sidespin. 右曲球是一种带有相当于顺时钟旋转导致剧烈向右弯曲的击球。 5. Slice the mushrooms thinly and fry in butter. 把蘑菇切成薄片,用黄油抄。', '形容词: sliceable 名词: slicer 过去式: sliced 过去分词: sliced 现在分词: slicing 第三人称单数: slices');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('segment', '[\'seɡmənt]', 'n.部分；弓形；瓣；段；节 vt.分割', '1. The company dominates this segment of the market. 这家公司控制了这一部分市场。 2. She cleaned a small segment of the painting. 她把画儿上的一小部分擦干净了。 3. The waiter brought us a dish of orange segments. 服务员给我们端来一盘掰开的橘子瓣。 4. Essentially, each segment is its own address space. 从本质上来说,每个段就是自己的地址空间。 5. Do you know how to segment an orange? 你知道怎么切橙子吗?', '形容词: segmentary 过去式: segmented 过去分词: segmented 现在分词: segmenting 第三人称单数: segments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infringe', '[ɪn\'frɪndʒ]', 'v.违反；侵犯', '1. We\'d better not infringe any of the rules. 我们还是不要违反规定才好。 2. They infringe the principle of non-discrimination. 他们违犯了非歧视原则。 3. They infringed on her rights. 他们侵犯了她的权力。 4. The publishing house infringed his copyright. 出版社侵犯了他的版权。', '名词: infringer 过去式: infringed 过去分词: infringed 现在分词: infringing 第三人称单数: infringes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hay', '[heɪ]', 'n.干草；<俚>一小笔钱；床', '1. The children snuggled down on the hay. 孩子们舒适地蜷伏在干草上。 2. Make hay while the sun shines. [谚]把握时机；趁热打铁。 3. The men hit the hay early, in order to be out hunting at dawn. 为了第二天破晓出去打猎，这些人很早就上床睡觉了。', '名词: hayer 过去式: hayed 过去分词: hayed 现在分词: haying 第三人称单数: hays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('onslaught', '[\'ɑːnslɔːt]', 'n.猛攻；攻击；抨击', '1. Our army tried to withstand the enemy onslaught. 我们的军队奋力抵挡敌人的猛攻。 2. The army took the fort on the first onslaught. 那支军队第一次突击就夺取了要塞。 3. The town survives the onslaught of tourists every summer. 每年夏天，这座小城都要熬过一段旅游者蜂拥而至的苦日子。 4. The central nervous systems survived the onslaught from the virus. 中央神经系统 承受了病毒的猛烈攻击', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('staggered', '[\'stæɡərd]', 'adj.非常吃惊的 动词stagger的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. I was staggered to hear/on hearing/when I heard of his death. 我听到他死的消息大吃一惊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clip', '[klɪp]', 'vt.夹住 v.剪短 v.疾驰；猛击 n.夹子；弹夹；回形针；钳 n.修剪；(羊毛的)剪下量；(被剪下的)东西', '1. Do you clip those ear-rings on/Do those ear-rings clip on 你的[这种]耳环是夹上去的吗? 2. There was a cheque clipped to the back of the letter. 在信背面夹着一张支票。 3. The dog\'s fur was clipped short for the show. 为参加狗展狗的毛剪短了。 4. A horse is clipping down the road. 一匹马正沿路奔驰。 5. Winston stroked his nose gently with a paper clip. 温斯顿用一个纸夹子轻轻地擦着鼻子。 6. He gave the sheep a close clip. 他把羊的毛剪得很短。', '过去式: clipped 过去分词: clipped 现在分词: clipping 第三人称单数: clips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sequoia', '[sɪ\'kwɔɪə]', 'n.红杉；巨杉', '1. Established in 1940, it contains giant sequoia trees. 1940年建立，园内有巨大的红杉树林。 2. What is the purpose of the giant sequoia tree? 巨杉树的用途是什么？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sew', '[soʊ]', 'v.缝合；缝纫', '1. The skirt is finished I\'m now going to sew a pocket on. 裙子做好了--我现在再缝上个口袋。 2. I\'ll just sew up that tear, and the coat will be as good as new. 我把大衣的破处缝好，就会完好如新了。 3. Sew that part all along. 把那部分从头到尾缝合起来。 4. Tack the folds down before you sew them firmly into place. 先用大针脚将褶子松松地缀住，然后再将其缝纫到位。', '形容词: sewable 过去式: sewed 过去分词: sewn/sewed 现在分词: sewing 第三人称单数: sews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quasar', '[\'kweɪzɑːr]', 'n.类星体', '1. The fuzzy object near top quasar image is the foreground galaxy. 靠近顶部类星体形象的模糊物体就是前景星系。 2. They do so by combining quasar spectra with numerical simulations of structure formation. 他们的做法是将类星体光谱和结构形成的数值模拟结果结合在一起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insufferable', '[ɪn\'sʌfrəbl]', 'adj.令人无法忍受的', '1. His insufferable insolence cost him many friends. 他那令人难以容忍的蛮横态度使他失掉了许多朋友。 2. The whole day long I hear nothing else but that I am an insufferable boy. 我整天听到的话全都是说我是个不可容忍的孩子。 3. I suppose I shall have to include my insufferable relatives in the wedding party. 恐怕我得把那些令人难以忍受的亲戚也都请到婚宴上。', '副词: insufferably 名词: insufferableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('erosion', '[ɪ\'rəʊʒn]', 'n.腐蚀；侵蚀；减少，流失', '1. Therefore, the corrosion was caused by erosion of rainwater during ocean shipping. 因此，这些腐蚀是海运途中雨水的浸蚀造成的。 2. The erosion of beach here is serious. 这里海岸的腐蚀很严重。 3. The cement petrified after many years\' erosion. 经过多年的侵蚀，水泥石化了。 4. The erosion of the soil is damaging the forest. 土壤侵蚀使得森林遭到了破坏。', '形容词: erosional 副词: erosionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('major', '[\'meɪdʒər]', 'adj.较多的；主要的；严重的；(音乐)大调的 n.成年人；主修（科目）；陆军少校；举足轻重者 v.主修', '1. The city holds the major portion of the population in the country. 那个城市聚集了全国大部分人口。 2. Popular education is one of our major objectives. 民众教育是我们的主要目标之一。 3. This quartet represents a major new trend in modern music. 这首四重奏的曲子反映了现代音乐中一种主要的新趋向。 4. We have encountered major problems. 我们已遇到重大的问题。 5. Majors should take more responsibilities and be more intelligent in handling personal relations. 成年人要承担更多的责任,在处理人际关系中也要变得更急灵活。 6. She majored in maths and physics at university. 她在大学期间主修数学和物理。', '过去式: majored 过去分词: majored 现在分词: majoring 第三人称单数: majors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deity', '[\'deɪəti]', 'n.神；神性 Deity. n.（前加the）上帝', '1. The evil deity has not yet revived compietely. 那邪恶的神他还没有苏醒。 2. Many animals were seen as the manifestation of a deity. 许多动物被看作神的化身。 3. Suppose one person gets into It by propitiating the Deity with hymns and worship, and you are pushed into It. 假如一个人陷入了里面，用诗歌和祷告来劝解神性，你也会被推进去。 4. The Deity is regarded as the perfect intelligence ruling over all of divine creation. 上帝被看作统治所有造物的具有完美智慧的神。', '名词复数: deities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barter', '[\'bɑːrtər]', 'v.物物交换；以货易货 n.物物交换；实物交易', '1. They used to barter for horses with salt. 他们过去以食盐交换马匹。 2. The colonists bartered calico for Indian land. 殖民者以印花布交换印地安人的土地。 3. The prisoners tried to barter with the guards for their freedom. 囚犯们企图和看守做换取自由的交易。 4. Some countries had to resort to barter to obtain foreign goods. 一些国家不得不采取以货易货的方法以得到外国货物。 5. On these islands a system of barter is used. 在这些岛上仍然实行着物物交换的制度。', '名词: barterer 过去式: bartered 过去分词: bartered 现在分词: bartering 第三人称单数: barters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tingle', '[\'tɪŋɡl]', 'n.刺痛；激动 v.刺痛；激动', '1. The cold caused a tingle in my ears. 严寒使我的耳朵有刺痛之感。 2. She feels a tingle of excitement. 她激动不已。 3. I tingle where I sat in the nettles. 我坐过在荨麻上的那个部位觉得刺痛。 4. XiaoLi\'s promise to marry him made his spine tingle. 小李答应与他结婚使他大为激动。', '形容词: tingly 名词: tingler 过去式: tingled 过去分词: tingled 现在分词: tingling 第三人称单数: tingles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('virus', '[\'vaɪrəs]', 'n.病毒；病原体', '1. Scientists have isolated the virus causing the epidemic. 科学家们已分离出引起这种流行病的病毒。 2. We should be watchful of computer viruses. 我们应该警惕计算机病毒。 3. HBV is a virus that causes inflammation of the liver. HBV是一种会引起肝脏发炎的病毒。 4. Could you do me a favor? My computer suffered from computer virus. 能帮帮我吗?我电脑中病毒了。', '名词复数: viruses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('angle', '[\'æŋɡl]', 'n.角度；角；观点 v.形成或转变角度；歪曲 v.钓鱼；谋取 Angle. n.盎格鲁人', '1. The rising sun is especially beautiful to look at from this angle. 旭日从这个角度看起来特别美。 2. Try looking at the affair from a different angle. 试从不同的角度来看这件事。 3. The two roads lie at an angle of about 45 degrees. 这两条路交叉成45度角。 4. We would like to hear your angle in this dispute. 我们想听听你在这场争论中的观点。 5. Angle the mirror so that you can see behind you. 调整镜子的角度,你可以看见你的后面。 6. He is keen on angling. 他喜欢钓鱼。', '过去式: angled 过去分词: angled 现在分词: angling 第三人称单数: angles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tint', '[tɪnt]', 'n. 色彩； 浅色； 染发剂 vt. 给 ... 染色', '1. Tint leaves the footage colors but wipes out darks. 著色使得画面的色彩，但清除掉深色衣物。 2. Today salt-loving bacteria thrive in brine pools on the dry lake bed, lending a blood-red tint in this aerial view. 如今，喜爱盐分的宅细菌在干涸湖床上的咸水池里繁茂生长，使得这幅空拍画面带着血红的色彩。 3. She gave me instructions on how to apply the tint. 她告诉我如何使用染发剂。', '名词: tinter 过去式: tinted 过去分词: tinted 现在分词: tinting 第三人称单数: tints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('supervise', '[\'suːpərvaɪz]', 'vt.监督；管理；指导', '1. I supervised the workers loading the lorry. 我监督工人把货物装上卡车。 2. The chief clerk supervises the work of the department. 文书组长负责监督该部门的工作。 3. She wants to supervise the cosmetics shop. 她想自己管理那间化妆品店。 4. How many people did you supervise on your last job? 你的上一份工作需要管理多少人?', '过去式: supervised 过去分词: supervised 现在分词: supervising 第三人称单数: supervises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gravel', '[\'ɡrævl]', 'n.碎石 v.铺碎石；使困惑', '1. The water is infiltrating the gravel bed. 水正渗透进碎石底层。 2. A lonely fisherman stood on a tuft of gravel. 一个孤单的渔夫站在碎石丛中。 3. Depressions are usually caused by heavy trucks passing over the gravel. 路面下沉通常是由路过铺碎石的重型卡车引起的。', '过去式: graveled/gravelled 过去分词: graveled/gravelled 现在分词: graveling/gravelling 第三人称单数: gravels/gravels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('profession', '[prə\'feʃn]', 'n.职业；声明；行业；信仰', '1. He is a doctor by profession. 他的职业是医生。 2. Nursing is a vocation as well as a profession. 护理工作既是职业又是救死扶伤的责任。 3. I don\'t believe her profession of friendship for us. 我不相信她声称同我们友好。 4. He is a leading member of the medical profession. 他是医疗业中首屈一指的医生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('visible', '[\'vɪzəbl]', 'adj.看得见的；可见的；显而易见的', '1. The big rafter is visible in this room. 这间屋子粗大的椽子可以看得见。 2. Various parts of his anatomy were clearly visible. 他身体的各个部分都看得很清楚。 3. The tower was visible from afar. 从远处就能望到那座塔。 4. The body was visible below the surface of the lake. 尸体在湖水下清晰可见。', '副词: visibly 名词: visibleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('condiment', '[\'kɒndəmənt]', 'n.调味品；佐料', '1. Fish sauce is a traditional fermented condiment in coastal areas. 鱼露是沿海地区的传统发酵调味品。 2. You then put condiment and a little salt into noodles. 然后你把佐料放进面条里，再加点盐。', '形容词: condimental');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trial', '[\'traɪəl]', 'n.审讯；试验；试用；尝试；预赛或选拔赛；讨厌的事；惹麻烦的人 v.测试', '1. He went through hell during the trial. 审讯期间他吃尽了苦头。 2. The flier is flying a new-type jet plane on trial. 飞行员正在驾驶一架新式喷气机作试验飞行。 3. She agreed to employ me for a trial period. 她同意试用我一段时间。 4. Trial and error is the source of our knowledge. 尝试和失败同是学识之源。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hubbub', '[\'hʌbʌb]', 'n.嘈杂；喧哗', '1. The hubbub of voices drowned out the host\'s voice. 嘈杂的声音淹没了主人的声音。 2. It was difficult to hear what he was saying over the hubbub. 声音太嘈杂，难以听清楚他的讲话。 3. At lunchtime, a pleasant hubbub of voices fills the museum\'s cafeteria. 午餐时间,博物馆的餐厅里洋溢着一片愉快的嘈杂声。 4. There arose a hubbub among them. 他们发出了一阵喧哗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remarkable', '[rɪ\'mɑːrkəbl]', 'adj.非凡的；值得注意的；显著的；异常的；卓越的', '1. The book is filled with remarkable insights. 这本书很有真知卓见。 2. He showed remarkable courage when he faced the danger. 他在面对危险的时候表现出非凡的勇气。 3. The changes taking place in China is remarkable. 中国发生的变化是值得注意的。 4. Science has made remarkable progress. 科学有了显著的进步。', '副词: remarkably 名词: remarkableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opposed', '[ə\'poʊzd]', 'adj.反对的；对立的；敌对的 动词oppose的过去式及过去分词.', '1. We are strongly opposed to racial discrimination. 我们强烈反对种族歧视。 2. The populace at large are opposed to sudden change. 人民群众普遍反对突然实行的变革。 3. Our previously opposed views are beginning to converge. 我们原来相互对立的观点开始趋於一致。 4. One of the armies opposed to the emperor was scattered to the winds already. 和皇帝敌对的一支军队，已被击溃了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deterrent', '[dɪ\'tɜːrənt]', 'adj.威慑的 n.威慑物；妨碍物，障碍', '1. Forest science presents many vivid and deterrent examples. 林业科学提供了许多生动的，引以为戒的例子。 2. Their missiles are viewed as a defensive and deterrent force. 他们的导弹被视为一种防卫和威慑力量。 3. His punishment will be a deterrent to others. 惩罚他以儆效尤。 4. Nuclear weapons are the ultimate deterrent. 核武器是终极的威慑力量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('leak', '[liːk]', 'v.渗；漏；泄露 n.漏洞；泄露', '1. Water had started to leak into the cellar. 水已开始渗入地下室。 2. The kitchen roof is apt to leak when it rains. 厨房的屋顶下雨时容易漏雨。 3. The details were supposed to be secret but somehow leaked out. 这些细节原属秘密，可是不知怎么给泄露出去了。 4. There is a leak in the roof. 屋顶有一个漏洞。', '名词: leaker 过去式: leaked 过去分词: leaked 现在分词: leaking 第三人称单数: leaks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('breakthrough', '[\'breɪkθruː]', 'n.突破，突破性进展；关键问题的解决', '1. It is a major technological breakthrough. 这是一次重要的技术突破。 2. He finally has a breakthrough in his creation. 他终于在创作上有了突破。 3. The scientists strive for a breakthrough in cancer research. 科学家们力争在癌症研究方面有个突破。 4. The medical breakthrough proves that guzzling ale is not the only reason why men develop saggy stomachs. 医学上的这一突破表明，男人们的啤酒肚并不完全是因为狂饮啤酒而造成的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subsist', '[səb\'sɪst]', 'v.供给食物；维持生活；生存；供养', '1. He subsisted mainly on vegetables and fruit. 他主要靠蔬菜和水果维持生命。 2. Don\'t worry about your children whom I can subsist. 别担心你的孩子们，我可以供养他们。 3. How do they manage to subsist on such a low wage? 他们这点工资怎么糊口？ 4. She has to get a casual work to subsist. 她不得不找一个临时工作维持生活。', '名词: subsister 过去式: subsisted 过去分词: subsisted 现在分词: subsisting 第三人称单数: subsists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('administer', '[əd\'mɪnɪstər]', 'vt.管理；执行；给与；用(药) vi.执行管理人职责；给与帮助', '1. He administered a large pension fund. 他管理一大笔养老金。 2. It takes brains to administer a large corporation. 管理大公司要有头脑。 3. The courts administer the law. 法院执行法律。 4. The government says it will administer relief to famine victims. 政府表示将向饥民发放救济品。 5. A administers upon the estate of B. 甲负责管理乙的遗产。', '形容词: administrable 过去式: administered 过去分词: administered 现在分词: administering 第三人称单数: administers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crater', '[\'kreɪtər]', 'n.坑(陨石坑、弹坑等)；凹地；火山口', '1. They blasted a huge crater in the runway. 他们在飞机跑道上炸了一个大坑。 2. The depth of the crater is expected to be about 30 feet. 弹坑的深度预计约于30英尺。 3. Lava boiled up from the crater of the volcano. 熔岩从火山口沸腾着升起来。 4. Flames blazed out from the crater of the volcano. 火焰从火山口猛烈地喷出来。', '过去式: cratered 过去分词: cratered 现在分词: cratering 第三人称单数: craters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arid', '[\'ærɪd]', 'adj.干燥的；不毛的；枯燥的；无趣的；没有生气的', '1. The broom grows down the arid sandhill. 金雀草蔓延在干燥的沙丘下。 2. It is difficult to grow fruit in arid desert areas. 在干燥的沙漠地带栽培水果很困难。 3. How can people make a living in this arid area? 这片不毛之地上的人们怎么谋生呢？ 4. The audience soon grew tired of his arid speech. 没多久听众对他枯燥无味的演说就感到厌腻了。', '名词: aridity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('merge', '[mɜːrdʒ]', 'v.合并；融合；兼并', '1. His department will merge with mine. 他的部门将和我的合并。 2. The two marching columns moved closer and finally merged. 行进中的两路纵队越走越近，终于合成一路。 3. The shadows slowly merge together. 这些阴影慢慢地融合在一起了。 4. The water and the sky merge into a pure whole. 水与天连成一线,不染纤尘。', '名词: mergence 过去式: merged 过去分词: merged 现在分词: merging 第三人称单数: merges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pump', '[pʌmp]', 'n.泵；抽水机；打气筒；抽水；打气 v.打气；唧筒般运动；灌输；抽取；增加；<口>盘问', '1. The heart has acted as a strong pump. 心脏充当了一部强有力的泵。 2. At the farm there was an old-fashioned pump for drawing water from a well. 那个农场有一台老式的用来从井里抽水的抽水机。 3. Can you lend me your bicycle pump? 能把你的打气筒借给我吗？ 4. After several pumps, the water began to flow. 用泵抽了几下之后,水流出来了。 5. Pump the tire up hard before going out on the road. 在出去上路之前, 要把轮胎打足气。', '名词: pumper 过去式: pumped 过去分词: pumped 现在分词: pumping 第三人称单数: pumps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evacuate', '[ɪ\'vækjueɪt]', 'v.疏散；撤出；排泄', '1. There\'s been a bomb threat we need to evacuate. 有人威胁说在这安放了炸弹 我们需要紧急疏散 2. Please evacuate the building immediately. 请立刻自大楼疏散。 3. The first priority shall be to evacuate the bus. 汽车着火后的第一要务是疏散乘客。 4. All people would evacuate the area. 所有人员也都全部撤离这一地区。', '形容词: evacuative 名词: evacuator 过去式: evacuated 过去分词: evacuated 现在分词: evacuating 第三人称单数: evacuates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fort', '[fɔːrt]', 'n.堡垒；要塞', '1. The men in the fort sallied at dawn. 堡垒里的人在黎明时出击。 2. They built an adobe fort, which is now a museum. 他们建造的泥砖堡垒，现已成为博物馆。 3. The enemy soon occupied the fort. 敌人很快占领这座要塞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hasten', '[\'heɪsn]', 'v.催促；赶快；加速', '1. Please hasten them to send the sample. 请催促他们寄来样品。 2. Do not hasten to bid me adieu. 不要告别得那样匆忙。 3. She hastened home after hearing the news. 听到这个消息后，她匆匆忙忙地回家。 4. Let me hasten to say that I could never do such a thing! 让我赶快说我永远不能做这样的事情！', '过去式: hastened 过去分词: hastened 现在分词: hastening 第三人称单数: hastens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('archaic', '[ɑːr\'keɪɪk]', 'adj.已不通用的；古老的；古代的', '1. The students are seeing the archaic film. 学生们在看那部古老的电影。 2. Their taste and style were archaic. 他们的情趣与风格都是古老的。', '副词: archaically 异体字: archaical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plateau', '[plæ\'toʊ]', 'n.高原；平稳；稳定状态 vi.到达平稳阶段', '1. The plateau extends for many miles. 高原连绵许多英里。 2. The ranch is in the middle of a large plateau. 该牧场位于一个辽阔高原的中部。 3. After a period of rapid inflation, price have now reach a plateau. 经急剧通货膨胀之后物价现已趋于平稳。 4. Mortgage rates declined, then reached a plateau. 抵押价格下跌，然后达到稳定水平 5. The athletic footwear market has not yet plateaued. 运动鞋市场并没趋于平稳。', '名词复数: plateaus 过去式: plateaued 过去分词: plateaued 现在分词: plateauing 第三人称单数: plateaus');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instigate', '[\'ɪnstɪɡeɪt]', 'vt.教唆；怂恿；煽动；鼓动', '1. They instigated him to the evil deed. 他们教唆他做坏事。 2. He wouldn\'t throw the rock if that boy did not instigate him. 要不是那些男孩子怂恿他,他不会扔那块石头。 3. He instigated the ending of a free working lunch in the company. 他煽动取消公司的免费工作午餐。 4. He accused union leaders of instigating the disturbances. 他指责工会领导鼓动骚乱。', '形容词: instigative 名词: instigation 过去式: instigated 过去分词: instigated 现在分词: instigating 第三人称单数: instigates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('simultaneous', '[ˌsaɪml\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.同时发生的；同步的', '1. The explosion was timed to be simultaneous with the plane\'s take-off. 爆炸的时间定在飞机起飞的时刻。 2. The simultaneous demonstrations are held in London and New York. 在伦敦和纽约同时举行示威游行。 3. There were several simultaneous attacks by the rebels. 反叛者同时发动了几起攻击。 4. Her work as a simultaneous translator requires strong powers of concentration. 作为同步翻译员，她的工作需要极大的专注力。', '副词: simultaneously 名词: simultaneousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interest', '[\'ɪntrəst]', 'n.兴趣；嗜好；利息；股份 v.使…感兴趣', '1. He showed not a spark of interest in the plan. 他对这个计划一点不感兴趣。 2. His two great interests in life are music and painting. 音乐和绘画是他生活中的两大嗜好。 3. Do you pay interest on that account? 那种存款付给利息吗? 4. He has an interest in the company. 他在这家公司拥有股份。 5. Things of that nature do not interest me. 我对那种事物不感兴趣。', '过去式: interested 过去分词: interested 现在分词: interesting 第三人称单数: interests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('guise', '[ɡaɪz]', 'n.装束；外观；伪装；借口', '1. They spoke to me under the guise of friendship. 他们伪装成友善的样子对我说话。 2. But tyranny also appeared in another guise. 但是暴政总是伪装成另一种形式。 3. Some will be based on misjudgments, and others will simply be pretextual - justifying aggression under the guise of pre-emption. 一些情况可能是建立在判断错误的基础上，其他情况只是借口，即在预防的伪装下试图证明进攻的正当性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('request', '[rɪ\'kwest]', 'n.请求；要求 vt.请求；要求', '1. I will oblige any sincere request. 我会答应任何诚意的请求。 2. His answer to my request was a negative. 我的请求遭到了他的拒绝。 3. Your request will be dealt with in due course. 你的要求将在适当时机予以处理。 4. I bought it at your request. 我应你的要求买下来。 5. We request you to deduct our commission from the invoice. 我们请求你方从发票中扣除我们的佣金。', '名词: requester 过去式: requested 过去分词: requested 现在分词: requesting 第三人称单数: requests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abate', '[ə\'beɪt]', 'v.缓和；减弱；消除', '1. Nothing could abate his rage. 什么都不能平息他的愤怒。 2. She is trying to abate the tension between her parents. 她试着缓和她父母的紧张关系。 3. The ship sailed when the storm abated. 这船在暴风雨减弱时起航。 4. Nothing can abate the force of that argument. 什么也不能减弱那场辩论的影响力。', '过去式: abated 过去分词: abated 现在分词: abating 第三人称单数: abates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sedentary', '[\'sednteri]', 'adj.久坐的；固定不动的', '1. People in sedentary jobs need to take exercise. 工作上要久坐的人需要做运动。 2. We should do away with the sedentary lifestyle. 我们应该抛弃久坐的生活方式。', '副词: sedentarily 名词: sedentariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pack', '[pæk]', 'n.一群；一副；包裹；一包 v.包装；解雇；塞满；收拾行李；佩戴', '1. The hare could find no safety, a pack of jackals had it in the wind. 野兔无处逃生,一群豺狗在追踪它。 2. He rounded on journalists, calling them \'a pack of vultures\'. 他突然对记者们大发雷霆，称他们是一帮贪婪的家伙。 3. A pack of cards has been spread on the table. 一副牌在桌被传播了。 4. Try to pair this card with one exactly the same from the other pack. 设法从另一副牌中取出一张和这张完全一样的牌。 5. In order to avoid any possible damage in transit, we would ask you to pack the goods in strong but small wooden cases. 为避免运送过程中的任何损坏,我方希望贵方用牢固且小巧的木箱来包装这些货物。', '形容词: packable 名词: packability 过去式: packed 过去分词: packed 现在分词: packing 第三人称单数: packs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('retrieve', '[rɪ\'triːv]', 'vt.恢复；挽回；取回 vi.找回猎物 n.恢复；取回；救出险球', '1. The company is fighting to retrieve its market share. 这个公司正在为恢复其市场份额(占有率)而奋斗。 2. She tried to retrieve the situation by making profuse apologies. 她不住的道歉,力图挽回局面。 3. I should like to retrieve my umbrella which I left in the car. 我想取回我留在车上忘记带走的雨伞。 4. The dog is trained to retrieve. 这狗受过训能找到并带回猎物。 5. This is a loss beyond retrieve. 这是无可挽回的损失。', '形容词: retrievable 副词: retrievably 名词: retrievability 过去式: retrieved 过去分词: retrieved 现在分词: retrieving 第三人称单数: retrieves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indefinite', '[ɪn\'defɪnət]', 'adj.模糊的；不确定的；无限期的', '1. He gave me an indefinite answer. 他给我的答复模棱两可。 2. He has rather indefinite views on the question. 他对该问题的看法颇暧昧。 3. She\'ll be away for an indefinite period. 她将离开一段时间，何时回来未定。 4. The union gave notice of indefinite strike. 工会通知无限期罢工。', '副词: indefinitely 名词: indefiniteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('series', '[\'sɪriːz]', 'n.（单复同）系列；丛书；连续', '1. The lecture series falls naturally into three parts. 该系列讲座可自然分作三部分。 2. The theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions. 这一理论是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。 3. He published a new series of readers for students of English. 他出版了一套新的英语学习丛书。 4. After a series of unsuccessful attempts, he has finally passed the driving test. 经过连续几次的失败，他最后终于通过了驾驶考试。', '名词复数: series');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unveil', '[ˌʌn\'veɪl]', 'vt.揭开；公布 vi.揭开', '1. Please unveil the label firstly. 请先揭开标签。 2. Women must not unveil themselves in public in Islamic societies. 在伊斯兰教国家里，妇女们在公共场合不能揭开面纱。 3. The president has two weeks from that date to unveil his new Cabinet. 总统在那之后有两星期时间公布他的新内阁。 4. Please unveil the label firstly. 请先揭开标签。', '过去式: unveiled 过去分词: unveiled 现在分词: unveiling 第三人称单数: unveils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('priority', '[praɪ\'ɔːrəti]', 'n.优先权；优先；优先顺序', '1. This is the key and should be given top priority. 这是关键，要放在第一位。 2. Efficiency does not always have priority. 效率不一定总是优先。 3. Improving the plight of teachers is indeed a priority item. 改善教师的困难处境的确是优先处理的一件事情。', '名词复数: priorities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insist', '[ɪn\'sɪst]', 'vt.坚持；坚决主张 vi.坚持；强调', '1. He insisted that he had done right. 他坚决认为自己做对了。 2. They insist that I stay there for supper. 他们坚决要求让我留下吃晚饭。 3. Since you insist, I must amend the letter of credit. 既然你坚持，我就只好修改信用证。 4. He insisted on paying for the meal. 他坚持要付饭钱。', '副词: insistingly 名词: insistence 过去式: insisted 过去分词: insisted 现在分词: insisting 第三人称单数: insists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('endorse', '[ɪn\'dɔːrs]', 'vt.赞同；支持；背书于', '1. I am afraid I can\'t endorse your opinion. 很抱歉，我不赞成你的意见。 2. I fully endorse their approach. 我完全赞同他们的工作方针。 3. I would like to endorse any choice you make. 我愿意认可你做出的任何选择。 4. He\'s had his license endorsed for dangerous driving. 他的驾驶执照上载有危险驾驶记录。', '形容词: endorsable 异体字: indorse 名词: endorser 过去式: endorsed 过去分词: endorsed 现在分词: endorsing 第三人称单数: endorses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abstain', '[əb\'steɪn]', 'v.戒绝；弃权；节制', '1. He swore to abstain from smoking. 他发誓要戒烟。 2. A high percentage of women said they had abstained from alcohol during pregnancy. 很大比例的妇女称他们在怀孕期间戒了酒。 3. I abstained from voting. 我弃权不投票。 4. Six countries voted for the change, five voted against, and two abstained. 六个国家投票赞成改变，五个反对，还有两个弃权。', '名词: abstainer 过去式: abstained 过去分词: abstained 现在分词: abstaining 第三人称单数: abstains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('demanding', '[dɪ\'mændɪŋ]', 'adj.要求多的；吃力的 动词demand的现在分词.', '1. Teaching is a demanding profession. 教学工作是个要求很高的工作。 2. Certainly I can agree with you that such duty is both dangerous and demanding. 我当然能同意你的看法，这种任务既危险，要求又严格。 3. During that time, messages on the picket signs became more demanding. 在那个时候，抗议海报上的要求也越来越积极。 4. He is a demanding child. 他是个很难满足的孩子。', '副词: demandingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deal', '[diːl]', 'n.协定；交易；大量 v.应付；分配；处理；交易；经营', '1. We did a deal with the management on overtime. 在加班问题上我们与管理部门达成一项协议。 2. After weeks of negotiating, they\'re finalizing the deal today. 经过几周协商,他们今天会搞定交易。 3. In addition to leaves, these animals eat a great deal of fruit. 除了树叶之外,这些动物还吃大量的水果。 4. If the worst comes to the worst, we can always deal with it. 事情再糟,我们总可以应付。', '过去式: dealt 过去分词: dealt 现在分词: dealing 第三人称单数: deals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conductivity', '[ˌkɒndʌk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.[物]传导性；传导率', '1. Electrical conductivity is affected by exposure to light. 导电性受光暴露的影响。 2. Thermal conductivity varies for different gases. 热传导率因不同气体而异。 3. Germanium has higher electric conductivity than silicon. 锗的导电率比硅高。', '名词复数: conductivities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infrastructure', '[\'ɪnfrəstrʌktʃər]', 'n.基础；基础设施', '1. We actively press ahead with the infrastructure development plan. 我们积极推进基础建设计划。 2. Our city offer overseas investors services for production aside from infrastructure services. 我市除了向外国投资者提供基础设施外,还提供良好的生产服务设施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mat', '[mæt]', 'n.垫子；席子 v.编织；集结；铺席于 ... 上', '1. There are some clods of soil on the mat. 垫子上有些土块。 2. He lifted the mat and slid the key under (it). 他掀起垫子把钥匙悄悄放在下面。 3. I wiped my shoes on the mat before I came in. 我在进门前把鞋在垫子上擦了擦。 4. Scrape your shoes on the door mat before you come in. 进屋前先在门口擦鞋垫上擦一擦鞋子。 5. The swimmer\'s wet hair was matted together. 那游泳者的湿头发乱糟糟结成一团。', '过去式: matted 过去分词: matted 现在分词: matting 第三人称单数: mats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assassinate', '[ə\'sæsəneɪt]', 'v.暗杀，行刺', '1. A plot to assassinate the President was uncovered. 暗杀总统的阴谋被发觉。', '形容词: assassinative 名词: assassination 过去式: assassinated 过去分词: assassinated 现在分词: assassinating 第三人称单数: assassinates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scuba', '[\'skjuːbə]', 'abbr.水中呼吸器 (=Self-Contained Underwater Breathing Apparatus)', '1. Ned used to be a scuba diver and now he\'s gone to the other extreme and taken up hang gliding. 内德过去是一名深水潜水员，现在他已走到另一个极端，开始从事悬挂式滑行运动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yarn', '[jɑːrn]', 'n.纱；线；<口>故事 v.讲故事', '1. Wool fibers can be spun into yarn. 羊毛纤维可纺成纱。 2. The tailor was balling the yarn. 裁缝正在把线缠成线团。 3. We stayed up yarning until midnight. 我们讲故事一直讲到半夜才睡。 4. The old mariner liked to yarn about his sea adventures. 老水手喜欢讲他的海上奇遇。', '过去式: yarned 过去分词: yarned 现在分词: yarning 第三人称单数: yarns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('federal', '[\'fedərəl]', 'adj.联邦制的；联邦政府的；同盟的 n.联邦主义者；同盟盟友', '1. Switzerland is a federal republic. 瑞士是联邦制的共和国。 2. Expenditures by the Federal Government have been steadily pared. 联邦政府的开支正在逐渐削减。', '副词: federally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flay', '[fleɪ]', 'v.剥皮；去皮；抢夺；痛责', '1. A good shepherd must fleece his sheep but not flay them. 好牧人只剪羊毛，不剥羊皮。（不要杀鸡取卵） 2. He was going to flay that stranger with every trick known to the law. 他要用法律上所有的招数来痛斥那个陌生人。', '名词: flayer 过去式: flayed 过去分词: flayed 现在分词: flaying 第三人称单数: flays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seep', '[siːp]', 'v.渗出；渗漏 n.渗漏；小泉；水坑', '1. Blood was beginning to seep through the bandages. 血开始从绷带上渗出来。 2. Oil is seeping out through a crack in the tank. 油箱的裂缝漏出油来了。 3. The teacher stopped speaking to allow time for the meaning of his words to seep through. 那位老师停止讲话，以便留出时间(让学生们)理解他所讲的意思。', '过去式: seeped 过去分词: seeped 现在分词: seeping 第三人称单数: seeps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('occupy', '[\'ɑːkjupaɪ]', 'vt.占用；占领；从事；使忙碌；专心', '1. Is that seat occupied? 那个座位有人吗？ 2. Reading occupies most of my free time. 阅读占去了我大部分的闲暇时间。 3. We occupy the farm and raise a lot of poultry. 我们拥有这个农场并养着许多家禽。 4. The enemy occupied the town. 敌人占据了这个城镇。', '名词: occupier 过去式: occupied 过去分词: occupied 现在分词: occupying 第三人称单数: occupies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('endanger', '[ɪn\'deɪndʒər]', 'vt.危及；危害', '1. It was foolish to endanger your life in that way. 用那种方式危及你的生命是愚蠢的。 2. Development of the area would endanger wildlife. 开发这一地区将会危及到野生生物。 3. Overworking can endanger your health. 工作过度可能会危害你的健康。 4. He did it in the knowledge that it might endanger his life. 他做那件事时知道它可能危害他的生命。', '名词: endangerment 过去式: endangered 过去分词: endangered 现在分词: endangering 第三人称单数: endangers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sketch', '[skɛtʃ]', 'n.速写；素描；草图；概述 v.草拟；速写；(简略地)描绘', '1. He is working up a sketch into a picture. 他正在把一幅速写加工成一幅画。 2. He did a sketch of the ballet dancers. 他为这些芭蕾舞者画了一张素描。 3. He squiggled a sketch on the ground. 他在地上胡乱地画了个草图。 4. They only gave us a sketch of the whole event. 他们只向我们简略地介绍了整个事件。 5. Sadly Mr Obama has repeatedly failed to sketch out how he might go about that. 遗憾的是,奥巴马再一次没能草拟出一份解决这一问题的方案。', '名词: sketcher 过去式: sketched 过去分词: sketched 现在分词: sketching 第三人称单数: sketches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('economics', '[ˌiːkə\'nɑːmɪks]', 'n.经济学', '1. She is studying economics at college. 她在大学里读经济学。 2. When they start talking about economics, I\'m out of my depth. 他们一谈起经济学，我就一窍不通了。 3. A knowledge of economics is fundamental to any understanding of this problem. 经济知识对于理解这个问题是至关重要的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('whim', '[wɪm]', 'n.一时的兴致；奇想', '1. I bought the encyclopedia on a whim. 我凭一时的兴致买了这本百科全书。 2. That suggestion was no whim of the moment. 那个建议可不是一时的突发奇想。 3. She bought that dress on a whim. 她一时心血来潮就买了那件连衣裙。 4. He dotes on his grandchildren and indulges their every whim. 他溺爱自己的孙辈,并且满足他们的任何想法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imprudent', '[ɪm\'pruːdnt]', 'adj.轻率的；不谨慎的', '1. It would be imprudent to resign from your present job before you are offered another. 还没有得到新的工作就辞去现有的工作太轻率了. 2. It is imprudent of you to lend money to a stranger. 你把钱借给陌生人,未免太不谨慎了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('explore', '[ɪk\'splɔːr]', 'v.探测；探险；考察；探究', '1. The experts are exploring every part of the island. 专家们正在勘查这个岛的各个部分。 2. He had an itch to get away and explore. 他等不及要动身去探险。 3. Can you explore the market possibility for us? 您能为我们考察一下市场前景吗？ 4. Columbus discovered America but did not explore the new continent. 哥伦布发现了美洲', '过去式: explored 过去分词: explored 现在分词: exploring 第三人称单数: explores 名词: exploration');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strive', '[straɪv]', 'vi.奋斗；努力；力求；斗争', '1. He strove for recognition as an artist. 他为获得艺术家的声誉而奋斗。 2. We should all strive to reunify the motherland. 我们共同努力,实现祖国统一。 3. I strive automatically to bring the world into harmony with my own nature. 我机械地努力以使这世界跟自己的性情协调一致。 4. The scientists strive for a breakthrough in cancer research. 科学家们力争在癌症研究方面有个突破。', '副词: strivingly 名词: striver 过去式: strove 过去分词: striven/strived 现在分词: striving 第三人称单数: strives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('satellite', '[\'sætəlaɪt]', 'n.卫星；人造卫星', '1. Troop movements can be observed from space by a satellite. 藉助卫星可观察到部队的调动。 2. The equipment picked up the signal from the satellite. 这设备收到了卫星发出的信号。 3. The bbc is hooked up with Australian television by satellite. 英国广播公司通过卫星与澳大利亚电视实行联播。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bulb', '[bʌlb]', 'n.球茎；电灯泡；球状物', '1. Onions and lilies grow from bulbs. 洋葱和百合是从球茎中长出的。 2. This light bulb has gone. 这灯泡不亮了。 3. The light bulb imploded. 这灯泡是向内侧爆裂的。 4. I can see clearly that the filament in the bulb is broken. 我可以很清楚地看到灯泡里的细丝断了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gloom', '[ɡluːm]', 'n.黑暗；阴暗；忧郁 v.(使)变黑；(使)变忧郁', '1. My eyes slowly grew accustomed to the gloom. 我的眼睛对黑暗慢慢适应了。 2. In the gloom I could only just discern the outline of a building. 在黑暗中我只能依稀分辨出一座建筑物的轮廓来。 3. He walked through the gloom of the thick forest. 他穿过茂密阴暗的森林。 4. The crimes committed there invested the place with an air of mystery and gloom. 在那里发生罪案后,该地笼罩上一种阴森诡秘的气氛。 5. Poets were often visited by fits of gloom. 诗人常有一阵阵忧郁。', '过去式: gloomed 过去分词: gloomed 现在分词: glooming 第三人称单数: glooms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unbiased', '[ʌn\'baɪəst]', 'adj.公正的', '1. The witness is unbiased and so reliable. 那个证人没有偏见, 因而是可靠的。 2. The credit rating agency shall ensure its rating unbiased and fair. 资信评级机构应保证其信用评级客观公正。', '副词: unbiasedly 名词: unbiasedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scrutinize', '[\'skruːtənaɪz]', 'v.仔细检查；细看', '1. We must scrutinize and evaluate. 我们必须细细察看并做出评价。 2. She leaned forward to scrutinize their faces. 她探身向前，端详他们的面容。 3. The boss came to scrutinize how things were going on for himself. 老板亲自详察工作进展情况。 4. All parts of the aircraft are closely scrutinized for signs of wear or damage. 飞机的所有部件都被仔细查看以防磨损和损坏。', '副词: scrutinizingly 名词: scrutinizer 过去式: scrutinized 过去分词: scrutinized 现在分词: scrutinizing 第三人称单数: scrutinizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('summary', '[\'sʌməri]', 'n.摘要；总结 adj.简略的；概要的；即决的', '1. Please write me a summary of this report. 请替我写一份这份报告的摘要。 2. Your summary will need fleshing out before you present it. 你的总结需要增加一些具体材料再交出。 3. I went through by a summary method. 我成功运用了一个简易的方法。 4. He gave a summary report of the day\'s events. 他对一天的事件作了简要的报告。', '副词: summarily 名词: summariness 名词复数: summaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('euphonious', '[juː\'foʊniəs]', 'adj.悦耳的', '1. He was enchanted with the euphonious music. 他陶醉在那悦耳的音乐中。 2. The euphonious sound of Carrie\'s cello playing always puts me at ease. 嘉莉悦耳的大提琴演奏总让我心旷神怡。', '副词: euphoniously 名词: euphoniousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('budge', '[bʌdʒ]', 'v. 移动； 妥协 n. 羔皮 adj. <古>浮夸的； 庄严的', '1. A cell can budge, however, only if it is able to synthesize a cytoskeleton, the network of fibers that gives it structural support. 可是细胞要想移动，它就必须合成细胞骨架，利用这种纤维网络才可支撑其结构。 2. Negotiations with the People\'s Alliance for Democracy have begun, but its leaders say they won\'t budge and will fight to the death. 同人民民主联盟的磋商已经开始，但是民盟领导人表示他们不会妥协，相反，他们会奋战到死。', '过去式: budged 过去分词: budged 现在分词: budging 第三人称单数: budges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accelerate', '[ək\'seləreɪt]', 'v.加速；提前；跳级', '1. Our present task is to accelerate economic growth. 加速经济发展是我们当前的任务。 2. The leader is losing ground as the rest of the runners accelerate. 领先者在其余赛跑者加速时就逐渐失去了优势。 3. We will accelerate the reform of the financial system under these circumstances. 在这一背景情况下,我们将加快金融体制改革。 4. The decline of her health seemed to suddenly accelerate. 她的健康状况好像突然提前衰退了。', '形容词: accelerative 过去式: accelerated 过去分词: accelerated 现在分词: accelerating 第三人称单数: accelerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corporate', '[\'kɔːrpərət]', 'adj.法人的；公司的；社团的；共同的；全体的', '1. This company is concerned about its corporate image. 这家公司关心它自身的法人形象。 2. The owner opened a corporate checking account at the bank. 公司老板在银行开了一个法人账户。 3. I\'d like to make an appointment to see your Corporate Finance Manager. 我想约见一下你们公司的财务经理。 4. This is our corporate responsibility. 这是我们共同的责任。', '副词: corporately');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chuckle', '[\'tʃʌkl]', 'v.轻声笑；咯咯笑；暗自笑 n.轻声笑；咯咯笑', '1. Cynics chuckle, and even Mr Paul sounds unenthusiastic about the Paulville project, in which he had no hand. 好挖苦的人轻声笑了，甚至保罗对这个保罗村项目听起来也不热心，因为他不参与这个项目。 2. Cynics chuckle, and even Mr Paul sounds unenthusiastic about the Paulville project, in which he had no hand. 好挖苦的人轻声笑了，甚至保罗对这个保罗村项目听起来也不热心，因为他不参与这个项目。', '形容词: chucklesome 副词: chucklingly 名词: chuckler 过去式: chuckled 过去分词: chuckled 现在分词: chuckling 第三人称单数: chuckles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('considerable', '[kən\'sɪdərəbl]', 'adj.重要的；相当大的；可观的', '1. The mayor is a considerable official. 市长是一位重要的官员。 2. He is a considerable person in that college. 他是那所学院相当重要的人物。 3. The economy was a considerable issue in the campaign. 在竞选运动中经济是一个重要问题。 4. His remarks provoked considerable comment. 他的话引起了相当大的议论。', '副词: considerably');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genius', '[\'dʒiːniəs]', 'n.天才；天赋', '1. He makes much account of her musical genius. 他重视她的音乐天才。 2. He is a mathematical genius. 他是一个数学天才。 3. Einstein was a mathematical genius. 爱因斯坦是数学天才。 4. His genius as a painter flowered very early. 他的绘画天赋很早就发挥出来。', '名词复数: geniuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('effectuate', '[ɪ\'fektʃueɪt]', 'vt.使实现', '1. The disease do not prevent him from effectuate his plan. 疾病并未妨碍他实现计划。 2. We do not have sufficient resources to effectuate our business. 我们没有足够的资源运作我们的业务。 3. A social program that was axed to effectuate budget cuts. 为实现预算削减而被无情去除的社会项目 4. In this part, we effectuate our performance by accomplishing the OEP approach. 在这一部分，我们通过完成OEP方法实现我们的执行。', '名词: effectuation 过去式: effectuated 过去分词: effectuated 现在分词: effectuating 第三人称单数: effectuates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aversion', '[ə\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.嫌恶；憎恨', '1. Girls generally have an aversion to snakes. 姑娘们通常对蛇很嫌恶。 2. Do you feel any aversion to hard study? 你嫌恶努力学习吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agenda', '[ə\'dʒendə]', 'n.议事日程', '1. This agenda will form the basis of our next meeting. 本议程将成为下次会议的中心议题。 2. Let\'s go on to the next item on the agenda. 我们讨论议程表上的下一项吧。 3. Let\'s thrash the matter over before putting it on the agenda. 我们先把这件事仔细研究一下，再把它列入议事日程。', '名词复数: agendas');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complicate', '[\'kɑːmplɪkeɪt]', 'v.使复杂化；使起纠纷 adj.复杂的', '1. There is no need to complicate matters. 没有必要使问题复杂化。 2. He always likes to complicate simple matters. 他总喜欢把简单的事情复杂化。 3. This text is more complicate than we can imagine. 这篇课文比我们想象的还要复杂。 4. My brother can understand the most complicate circuit diagrams. 再复杂的线路图哥哥都能看懂。', '过去式: complicated 过去分词: complicated 现在分词: complicating 第三人称单数: complicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('soft', '[sɔːft]', 'adj.柔软的；柔和的；温和的；不强烈的；轻的 adv.柔软地；温和地 n.柔软的东西', '1. The new leaves in springtime have a soft touch. 春天的新芽有柔软的触感。 2. It\'s very comfortable to step on the soft ground in the spring. 春天的时候，踩在松软的地面上非常舒服。 3. The room was flooded with soft light. 房间里充满了柔和的光。 4. The soft breeze stirs the leaves. 柔和的微风摇动着树叶。 5. He comforted his back with something soft. 他用柔软的东西使他的背部舒服一点。', '副词: softly 比较级: softer 最高级: softest 名词: softness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('debt', '[det]', 'n.债务；恩情；负债状态；义务；罪', '1. He promised to pay his debt within a month. 他保证在1个月内偿还债务。 2. If I pay all my debts I\'ll have no money. 我若还请所有欠债就分文不剩了。 3. We owe you a debt of gratitude for you help. 承蒙帮助，感恩不尽。 4. The company is deep in debt. 这家公司正负债累累。', '形容词: debtless');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('powder', '[\'paʊdər]', 'n.粉末；粉；火药；细雪 vt.洒粉于；使变成粉；重击 vi.变成粉；涂粉', '1. Borax is a kind of white powder. 硼砂是一种白色粉末。 2. There\'s too much powder on your nose. 你鼻子上的粉擦得太多了。 3. I know the smell of powder. 我上过战场。 4. Have you ever skied the powder in Utah? 你在犹他州滑过雪吗? 5. I\'m just going to powder my nose. 我想去补补妆。 6. Actors powder with their left hands for luck. 演员们为了讨吉利而用左手搽粉。', '名词: powderer 过去式: powdered 过去分词: powdered 现在分词: powdering 第三人称单数: powders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prevailing', '[prɪ\'veɪlɪŋ]', 'adj.盛行很广的；盛行的，广泛流传的；主流的', '1. He wore his hair in the prevailing fashion. 他的头发梳的是当时盛行的发型。 2. Your price is out of line with the prevailing international market. 你方价格与现行世界市场行情不一致。', '副词: prevailingly 名词: prevailingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('epidemic', '[ˌepɪ\'demɪk]', 'n.流行病；传染病 adj.流行的；传染性的', '1. A flu epidemic raged through the school for weeks. 流感在这所学校里蔓延了几个星期。 2. The small town was suddenly struck by an epidemic. 小镇突然遭到传染病的袭击。 3. Violence is reaching epidemic levels. 暴力达到了流行的程度。 4. The corruption has become epidemic in the society. 这种腐化已成为社会上的一种歪风。', '副词: epidemically 异体字: epidemical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('somewhat', '[\'sʌmwʌt]', 'adv.稍微；有些；多少；几分 pron.某物；一些', '1. Their swimming pool is somewhat deep than ours. 他们的游泳池比我们的游泳池稍微深一点儿。 2. The price was somewhat higher than I\'d expected. 这价格比我预料的稍高一些。 3. We are suffering somewhat from the heat. 我们因为酷热有些不好受。 4. His explanation overreached somewhat. 他的辩解多少有点过火。 5. The exact program of research we pursue will be somewhat driven by the people that we\'re able to attract. 精确的计画研究我们追求将会是被我们能够吸引的人驱使的某物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manifest', '[\'mænɪfest]', 'vt.显示；证实；表露 adj.明白的；显然的 n.旅客名单；载货单', '1. His generosity manifests itself in times of difficulties. 他的慷慨在困境中表现了出来。 2. Opportunities will manifest in ways you never even dreamed of. 机会的到来出乎你的意料。 3. No one can manifest the truth of his statement. 没人能证明他讲的是真话。 4. The contradiction manifested itself in the employment situation. 在就业问题上矛盾暴露了。 5. It was manifest to us at a glance. 我们对此事一目了然。 6. Can you give us a copy of import manifest? 能给我们一份进口舱单吗?', '副词: manifestly 过去式: manifested 过去分词: manifesed 现在分词: manifesting 第三人称单数: manifests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skyscraper', '[\'skaɪskreɪpər]', 'n.摩天大楼', '1. A new skyscraper has been put up downtown. 市中心又建起了一座摩天大厦。 2. The skyscraper towers into the sky. 该摩天大楼高耸入云。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('leftover', '[\'leftoʊvər]', 'n.剩饭；残留物 adj.残余的', '1. She threw the leftovers in the garbage. 她把剩饭倒进垃圾桶。 2. Give the leftovers to the dog. 把剩饭给狗吃。 3. He\'s a leftover from the hippies in the 1960s. 他是20世纪60年代嬉皮士的残余分子。 4. The leftover food began to smell bad. 剩饭开始发臭了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('baste', '[beɪst]', 'v.疏缝；痛斥；大骂；润以油脂；涂以奶油', '1. They bast me without any reason. 他们无缘无故地大骂我。 2. Mother used a large spoon to baste the chicken. 母亲在鸡肉上润以一大匙的油脂。 3. You must baste the duck with its own fat every time you turn the duck. 每次转换位置时，必须在整只鸭上涂满鸭身渗出的油脂。', '名词: baster 过去式: basted 过去分词: basted 现在分词: basting 第三人称单数: bastes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gem', '[dʒem]', 'n.宝石；珍品；受到宠爱或评价很高的人；松糕 vt.用宝石装饰', '1. He beguiled me into parting with the gem. 他诱骗我把那枚宝石割爱。 2. Saphhire is a very hard blue gem. 一种蓝色的非常坚硬的宝石。 3. This picture is the gem of the collection. 这幅画是收藏的珍品. 4. My secretary is an absolute gem. 我的秘书真是个难能可贵的人。', '过去式: gemmed 过去分词: gemmed 现在分词: gemming 第三人称单数: gems');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unbecoming', '[ˌʌnbɪ\'kʌmɪŋ]', 'adj.不合身的；不相称的；不适当的；不得体的', '1. She is wearing an unbecoming dress. 她穿着一条不合身的裙子。 2. He was drummed out of the service for conduct unbecoming of an officer. 他因行为与军官的身份不相称而被部队开除。 3. She felt that tears were unbecoming and foolish. 她觉得流泪是不适当的和愚蠢的。 4. It was thought to be unbecoming for young ladies to smoke. 年轻女子吸烟被认为是不得体的。', '副词: unbecomingly 名词: unbecomingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stagger', '[\'stæɡər]', 'vi.蹒跚；犹豫；动摇 vt.使摇晃；使吃惊；使犹豫 n.蹒跚；踌躇；摇摆不定', '1. She staggered and fell. 她踉跄了几步，跌倒在地。 2. The drunk man staggered across the room. 那个醉汉摇摇晃晃地穿过房间。 3. His resolution had begun to stagger. 他的意志开始动摇了。 4. Such a heavy load would stagger an elephant. 这么重的担子，大象担着也得摇晃。 5. He gave a stagger on hearing the news. 他听到这一消息两腿摇晃起来。', '形容词: staggery 名词: staggerer 过去式: staggered 过去分词: staggered 现在分词: staggering 第三人称单数: staggers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exert', '[ɪɡ\'zɜːrt]', 'vt.运用；施加', '1. He exerted all his influence to make them accept his plan. 他用尽一切影响力使他们接受他的计划。 2. He doesn\'t have to exert himself on my behalf. 他不必为我费那么大力气。 3. You have to exert more efforts if you want to catch up with your classmates. 你要想赶上你的同学的话,就得多花些功夫。 4. His teachings still exert a strong influence. 他的教导仍在产生巨大影响。', '过去式: exerted 过去分词: exerted 现在分词: exerting 第三人称单数: exerts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('landing', '[\'lændɪŋ]', 'n.着陆；登陆；登陆处；楼梯平台 动词land的现在分词.', '1. The plane circled the airport before landing. 飞机在着陆之前在机场上空盘旋。 2. He brought the aircraft\'s nose up and made a perfect landing. 他拉起机头，平稳地降落下来。 3. Then he ordered the landing of marines there. 于是他下令海军陆战队在那里登陆。 4. There is no safe landing on that coast. 那一带海岸没有安全的登陆处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anthropology', '[ˌænθrə\'pɑːlədʒi]', 'n.人类学', '1. His field of expertise was anthropology. 他的研究领域是人类学。 2. She\'s course tutor in anthropology. 她是人类学选课指导教师。 3. Anthropology is one of the social sciences. 人类学是社会科学中的一支。 4. I believe he has started reading up anthropology. 我相信他已开始攻读人类学。', '形容词: anthropological 副词: anthropologically 名词: anthropologist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wane', '[weɪn]', 'n.衰落；亏缺；变弱 v.变小；亏缺；呈下弦', '1. The empire was on the wane after its period of prosperity. 帝国经过全盛以后逐渐衰落。 2. By now the power of the Roman Empire was on the wane. 到这时，罗马帝国已日益衰败。 3. Why should the moon have wax and wane? 为什么一定会月有阴晴圆缺? 4. The sick man\'s strength is on the wane. 病人的体力越来越弱。 5. As time went on, so their hopes began to wane. 随着时间的消逝，他们的希望开始变得渺茫。', '过去式: waned 过去分词: waned 现在分词: waning 第三人称单数: wanes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cholesterol', '[kə\'lestərɔːl]', 'n.胆固醇', '1. This cooking oil is low in cholesterol. 这种烹调油胆固醇含量低。 2. Would you expect the cholesterol to be elevated? 你考虑胆固醇会升高吗? 3. There are many food products that claim to reduce cholesterol levels. 很多食品都宣称可以降低胆固醇水平。 4. A high cholesterol level in the blood can cause heart disease. 血液中胆固醇含量高可导致心脏病。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diversity', '[daɪ\'vɜːrsəti]', 'n.多样性；差异', '1. We should get a thorough understanding about the cultural diversity of the United States. 我们应该对美国文化的多样性有一个全面的了解。 2. Diversity is conducive to the learning environment. 多样化对学习环境确有益处。 3. India has huge diversity and could evolve into a trading club and become rich. 印度国内差异巨大,完全可能演变成一个自由贸易俱乐部,最终实现致富。', '名词复数: diversities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('audience', '[\'ɔːdiəns]', 'n.听众；观众；读者；倾听；拥护者；正式会见', '1. The audience was no less than five thousand. 听众有五千人之多。 2. Someone in the audience began to laugh. 观众中有人开始笑起来。 3. The concert drew a large audience. 音乐会吸引了大量的观众。 4. The article was put out in a national magazine to reach a larger audience. 为了能影响更多的读者,文章被登发在一份国家级杂志上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slip', '[slɪp]', 'v.滑倒；滑脱；疏忽；溜走 n.疏忽；滑倒；溜走；失误', '1. She slipped on the ice. 她在冰上滑倒了。 2. I was unlucky to slip on a banana skin and fall over. 我真倒霉，踩在香蕉皮上滑倒了。 3. The gear slipped. 齿轮滑脱了 4. The wheel slipped from my frozen hand, and the car went right across the road. 方向盘从我冻僵的手里滑脱, 汽车便横着穿过了马路。 5. Leaving his name off the list was a bad slip up. 名单上没有他的名字是个严重的疏忽。', '过去式: slipped 过去分词: slipped 现在分词: slipping 第三人称单数: slips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ephemeral', '[ɪ\'femərəl]', 'adj.短暂的；朝生暮死的 n.生存极短时间的事物', '1. Most newspapers are of ephemeral interest. 多数报纸只能引起读者短暂的注意。 2. Slang words are often ephemeral. 俚语往往只流行于一时。 3. Such novels came forward to enjoy ephemeral popularity only. 这样的小说只是昙花一现的东西而已。', '副词: ephemerally 名词: ephemerality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('steady', '[\'stedi]', 'adj.稳定的；稳固的；坚定的 v.使稳固；使稳定；(变得)稳固；使坚定 adv.稳定地，稳固地 n. 关系固定的情侣；固定支架', '1. The old man is not steady on his legs. 这位老人站不稳。 2. The agreement ensured a steady supply of oil. 该协定保证了石油的稳定供给。 3. Don\'t tell your secret to him before you get a steady relationship. 在未跟他的感情稳定下来之前,不要把自己的秘密说给他听。 4. I know she is steady in her purpose. 我知道她意志坚定。 5. She held onto a strap to steady herself. 她抓住拉手吊带以便站稳。', '副词: steadily 比较级: steadier 最高级: steadiest 名词: steadiness 名词复数: steadies 过去式: steadied 过去分词: steadied 现在分词: steadying 第三人称单数: steadies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prescribe', '[prɪ\'skraɪb]', 'v.开处方；规定，命令，指示；限制，限定', '1. I\'ll prescribe for you as soon as I get the report. 我拿到报告就给你开处方。 2. What medicine did the doctor prescribe for your illness? 医生开了什么药来治你的病？ 3. The law prescribes heavy penalties for this offence. 法律规定对这种不法行为从严惩处。 4. Regulations prescribe that a lawyer draw up the paper. 条文规定必须由律师拟定此公文。', '名词: prescriber 过去式: prescribed 过去分词: prescribed 现在分词: prescribing 第三人称单数: prescribes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oath', '[oʊθ]', 'n.誓言；誓约；咒骂语', '1. Repeat the oath after me. 请跟着我宣誓。 2. The judge received their oath of allegiance. 法官听取了他们的忠诚誓言。 3. Tom stood by his oath to his father. 汤姆遵守他给父亲立下的誓言。 4. She carries an oath rod that will destory the minds of those it strikes. 她携带着一根誓约之杖，能够摧毁所有被杖击中者的意识。', '名词复数: oaths');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sunlit', '[\'sʌnlɪt]', 'adj.被日光照射的', '1. Her house has two big sunlit rooms with floor-to-ceiling windows. 她的房子里有两间向阳的房间，并且有落地大窗。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irritable', '[\'ɪrɪtəbl]', 'adj.易怒的；急躁的', '1. The old man is an irritable person. 那个老人是个易怒的人。 2. We were both workaholics who got more irritable when we were exhausted. 我们都是工作狂，疲惫不堪的时候脾气越发暴躁。 3. Our teacher is an irritable old lady. She gets angry easily. 我们的老师是位脾气急躁的老太太。她很容易生气。', '副词: irritably 名词: irritableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('square', '[skwer]', 'n.正方形；广场；街区；平方；直角尺；<俚>古板的人 adj.正方形的；规矩的；结实的；公正的；断然的 v.一致；结清；收买；使 ... 成方形；使成平方；调整 adv.成直角；直接的；正方形地', '1. The little girl drew a square on the paper. 小女孩在纸上画了一个正方形。 2. Everybody goes to this vast square in the evening. 每天傍晚，人人都上这宽阔的广场上来。 3. The crowds in the square were elated by the news. 这消息使广场上的人群欢欣鼓舞。 4. 25 is a perfect square of 5. 25是5的完全平方。 5. A handkerchief is usually square. 手帕通常是正方形的。 6. His conduct does not square with his words. 他言行不一致。 7. The road turned square to the left. 这条路成直角向左转去。', '副词: squarely 比较级: squarer 最高级: squarest 名词: squareness 过去式: squared 过去分词: squared 现在分词: squaring 第三人称单数: squares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('military', '[\'mɪləteri]', 'adj.军事的 n.军队', '1. They are making further efforts to decrease military spending. 他们正在做进一步的努力来减少军费开支。 2. In some countries all the young men do a year\'s military service. 有些国家，所有年轻男子都要服一年兵役。 3. The military were called in to deal with the riot. 已将军队调来镇压暴乱。 4. The military has tightened its hold on the country. 军方加强了对这个国家的控制。', '副词: militarily 名词复数: military');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('premise', '[\'premɪs]', 'n.前提 vt.预述；提论；假设', '1. I wonder whether the whole premise is right. 我怀疑整个前提是否正确。 2. We must act on the premise that the worst can happen. 我们必须在可能发生最坏事态的前提下行动。 3. British justice works on the premise that an accused person is innocent until he\'s proved guilty. 英国司法运作的前提是被告在被证明有罪之前是清白的。 4. You had better premise your argument with a little historical knowledge. 你最好引述一些历史知识作为你立论的前提。', '过去式: premised 过去分词: premised 现在分词: premising 第三人称单数: premises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spontaneous', '[spɑːn\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.自发的，自然的，本能的；自然产生的', '1. He is spontaneous to offer help. 他主动提供帮助。 2. It is a spontaneous cheer from the crowd. 那是群众自发的喝彩。 3. The spontaneous applause cut the singer short. 自发的掌声打断了歌唱家的演唱。 4. The eruption of volcanoes is spontaneous. 火山爆发是自然产生的。', '副词: spontaneously 名词: spontaneousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mimicry', '[\'mɪmɪkri]', 'n.模仿；(动物等)拟态伪装', '1. Language learning usually necessitates conscious mimicry. 一般地说,学习语言就要进行有意识的模仿。 2. Best mimicry too can generate the imitation article, not genuine calligraphy. 最好的模仿也只能产生赝品，而不是真迹。 3. Mimicry in plants or animals is a three-part system. 动植物的拟态包括三方面的内容。', '名词复数: mimicries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('potassium', '[pə\'tæsiəm]', 'n.钾', '1. The components of a potassium cycle vary greatly. 钾素循环的各个环节有很大的变化。 2. What fruit vegetable contains potassium most? 什么水果蔬菜含钾最多？', '形容词: potassic 简写符号: K');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pioneer', '[ˌpaɪə\'nɪr]', 'n.先锋；开拓者；先驱 v.开辟；首倡', '1. He was a pioneer in the use of X-rays. 他是最早使用X光的人。 2. I see everybody as a pioneer out there. 我认为每个人在那里都是先锋。 3. She was descended from a pioneer family. 她来自一个早期的开拓者家庭 4. He is a pioneer in modern medical practice. 他是现代医学实践的先驱。 5. She pioneered the use of the drug. 是她最先使用的这种药品。', '过去式: pioneered 过去分词: pioneered 现在分词: pioneering 第三人称单数: pioneers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bony', '[\'boʊni]', 'adj.如骨的；多骨的；瘦骨嶙峋的', '1. A high bony fin was cutting through the water toward him. 一个高高的骨状鱼鳍正划破水面，向他追来。 2. That steak is bony and difficult to eat. 那种牛排多骨, 很不易吃。 3. The secretary is a tall and bony man. 秘书是个又高又瘦的男子。 4. He eats so little that he is bony. 他吃得太少, 瘦得只剩皮包骨。', '异体字: boney 比较级: bonier/boneyer 最高级: boniest/boneyest 名词: boniness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conspicuous', '[kən\'spɪkjuəs]', 'adj.显著的；显眼的；显而易见的', '1. Lincoln is a conspicuous example of a poor boy who succeeded. 林肯是一个穷苦孩子而功成名就的出色例子。 2. He was conspicuous for his bravery. 他因骁勇而出名。 3. A traffic sign should be conspicuous. 交通标志应该明显。 4. Notices shall be put in conspicuous places. 要保证把布告贴在显眼的地方。', '副词: conspicuously 名词: conspicuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('parasite', '[\'pærəsaɪt]', 'n.寄生虫；寄生生物；食客', '1. Rupture of the parasite may result in anaphylaxis. 寄生虫的碎裂可能导致过敏反应。 2. These flies carry a dangerous parasite. 这些苍蝇携带一种危险的寄生虫。 3. The parasite\'s host could be any bird. 该寄生生物的宿主可以是任何鸟类。 4. The result is a repeated signal, and a new limb forms in addition to the one to which the parasite attached itself. 这样的结果将是一种持续的讯号，而一种被寄生生物附著在肢体上所产生的新的生长型态将应运而生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('awe', '[ɔː]', 'n.敬畏；恐惧 vt.使敬畏；使惊惧', '1. The children stared at the teacher with awe. 孩子很敬畏地凝视着老师。 2. We all listened to the venerable scholar with awe. 我们都怀着敬畏之心倾听着这位德高望重的学者的讲话。 3. An unsought pathos came hand in hand with awe. 与恐惧相随而来的是一种意想不到的悲怆。 4. No difficulty could awe these young men. 任何困难都吓不倒这些年轻人。', '过去式: awed 过去分词: awed 现在分词: awing 第三人称单数: awes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brawl', '[brɔːl]', 'n.争吵；大声的吵闹 vi.争吵；大声喊；哗哗流', '1. He shall not get so angry. What we have gotten here is more like a brawl than a debate. 他不应该那么生气的。这里的样子不像在讨论而像是在吵架。 2. He is a timid boy; it\'s impossible for him to brawl with anyone. 他是一个胆小的男孩，他不可能和任何人吵架。 3. The young men had nothing better to do than brawl in the streets. 那些年轻人除了在街上打架外没更好的事干。 4. The river brawled over the rapids. 河水哗哗地流过湍滩。', '副词: brawlingly 名词: brawler 过去式: brawled 过去分词: brawled 现在分词: brawling 第三人称单数: brawls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('potter', '[\'pɑːtər]', 'n.陶工；陶艺家 vi.懒散；闲逛(=putter)；磨蹭地做一些琐事', '1. The potter shaped the clay into a vase. 陶工将泥土塑成花瓶。 2. A potter is making pottery by hand. 陶器匠正用手做陶器。 3. He loves to potter in the garden. 他喜欢在花园里随便走走。 4. We spent the weekend pottering around (in) the house. 我们周末做一些琐碎的家务事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('syrup', '[\'sɪrəp]', 'n.糖浆；甜而黏稠的汁液', '1. I cooked the syrup until it threaded. 我将糖浆熬到能抽丝为止。 2. Mother dosed the child up with cough syrup. 母亲让孩子按量服用止咳糖浆。 3. She dosed up the children with cough syrup. 她把止咳糖浆给孩子们吃了。 4. The maple sap was boiled down to a thick syrup. 枫树的汁液聚结为粘稠的浆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decode', '[ˌdiː\'koʊd]', 'v.解码；译解；译码', '1. Method is used to decode the array of bytes. 方法用来解码字节数组。 2. The Lab Activity will help students decode a waveform. 实验活动将帮助学生解码一道波形。', '名词: decoder 过去式: decoded 过去分词: decoded 现在分词: decoding 第三人称单数: decodes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('malleable', '[\'mæliəbl]', 'adj.可塑的；易改变的；有延展性', '1. Lead and tin are malleable metals. 铅和锡是可锻的金属。 2. The human brain is almost infinitely malleable. 人类大脑具有无限的可塑性。 3. The young are more malleable than the old. 年轻人比老年人容易受影响。 4. Every time we recall a long-term memory, it becomes malleable. 每次我们想起一个长期的记忆，它会变得有延展性。', '副词: malleably 名词: malleability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forthright', '[\'fɔːrθraɪt]', 'adj.直截的；直率的；坦白的', '1. She gave him a forthright answer. 她给了他一个坦率的答覆。 2. His forthright behavior offends some people. 他那直率的行为冒犯了某些人。 3. His forthright behaviour shows that he\'s honest, but he seems rude to some people. 他的直率行为说明他是个诚实的人，可是有些人却认为他粗鲁。 4. His frank and forthright action deserves praise. 他光明磊落的行为值得称赞。', '副词: forthrightly 名词: forthrightness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('besides', '[bɪ\'saɪdz]', 'prep.除 ... 之外 adv.此外；也', '1. No one writes to me besides you. 除你以外，没有人给我写信。 2. There will be five of us for dinner, besides John. 除约翰外，还有我们五个人要一起吃饭。 3. He has been to Mexico but nowhere besides. 他曾去过墨西哥但没去过别的地方。 4. He gave me a book,a pen and some money besides. 他给我一本书，一支钢笔，此外还给一些钱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('monarch', '[\'mɑːnərk]', 'n.帝王；统治者；君主 n.君王斑点蝶', '1. They attempted to overthrow the monarch. 他们企图推翻国王。 2. The national band played for the visiting monarch. 国家乐团演奏给来访的帝王听。 3. I think myself happier now than the greatest monarch upon earth. 我觉得这个时候比世界上什么帝王都快乐。 4. They also crowned Dath\'Remar as their first monarch. 他们拥护达斯雷玛成为他们的第一任皇权统治者。 5. I saw the monarch butterfly by accident. 我偶尔看见了君王斑点蝶。', '形容词: monarchal 副词: monarchally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skeleton', '[\'skelɪtn]', 'n.骨架；纲要；骨骼；骨瘦如柴的人或动物；家丑 adj.骨骼的', '1. The block is still just a skeleton of girders. 这片建筑还只是仅有主梁的骨架。 2. The director set out the plan in skeleton form. 主任提纲挈领地说明了这一计划。 3. I\'ve written the skeleton of my report, but I have to fill in the details. 我已写出报告的梗概，但我必须补充细节。 4. The shell of a snail is its skeleton. 蜗牛的壳是它的骨骼。 5. As a part of the whole skeleton, oral maxillofacial bone loss has some association with systemic osteoporosis. 做为全身骨骼的一部分，颌骨的骨丢失一直被认为与全身骨质疏松存在关联性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('effective', '[ɪ\'fektɪv]', 'adj.有效的；生效的；实际的', '1. Advertising is often the most effective method of promotion. 做广告往往是最有效的推销方法。 2. Their efforts to improve the production have been very effective. 他们提高生产力的措施卓有成效。 3. When does the new system become effective? 新制度何时生效？ 4. Her brother is the king, but she is the effective ruler. 她的兄弟是国王, 但她才是实际的主宰者。', '名词: effectiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('headstrong', '[\'hedstrɔːŋ]', 'adj.顽固的；刚愎的；任性的', '1. Mrs. Ferrars is a very headstrong, proud woman. 费拉尔斯太太是个非常顽固、傲慢的妇人。 2. The headstrong impetuous man rushed into things without forethought. 这个顽固的莽汉，不预先考虑，仓促行事。 3. She\'s hopelessly headstrong; she always gets up against people in authority. 她刚愎自用到了不可挽救的地步，老是与主管人员发生冲突。 4. We cannot tolerate his headstrong actions. 我们不能容忍他的任性行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tiny', '[\'taɪni]', 'adj.极小的；微小的', '1. A tiny fishing boat was drifting slowly along. 一只小小的渔船在缓缓地漂去。 2. We\'re struggling along on a tiny income. 我们依靠极少的收入过活。 3. She has a tiny mole on her cheek. 她面颊上有一颗小痣。 4. The baby\'s dress was beautifully tucked with tiny stitches. 婴儿衫的褶裥打得针脚细密，很漂亮。', '比较级: tinier 最高级: tiniest 名词: tininess');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cultivated', '[\'kʌltɪveɪtɪd]', 'adj.栽植的；有教养的 动词cultivate的过去式和过去分词.', '1. It is a pity to let this cultivated land lie idle. 这些耕地丢荒了，真让人可惜。 2. The cultivated area is being further extended. 耕地正进一步扩大。 3. This lady has always been gentle and cultivated. 这个女人素来温文尔雅。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sacred', '[\'seɪkrɪd]', 'adj.神圣的；受尊重的', '1. In India the cow is a sacred animal. 在印度，牛是神圣的动物。 2. We use them to protect our sacred grounds. 我们使用它们来保卫我们神圣的土地。 3. Nothing is sacred to these wild youths. 这些狂野的年轻人什么都不尊重。 4. This area was hallowed by sacred memories. 这个地区由于宗教上的纪念意义而被视为圣地。', '副词: sacredly 名词: sacredness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tycoon', '[taɪ\'kuːn]', 'n.企业界的大亨；（日本幕府的）将军', '1. The self-made tycoon was bragging about the secret of his success. 那位靠自我奋斗发了财的大亨正在夸耀他成功的秘诀。 2. Disgraced media tycoon Conrad Black will appeal against his convictions for fraud, his lawyer has said. 令人蒙羞的媒体企业界的大亨康拉德黑色将为诈欺不服他的定罪而上诉，他的律师已经说。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alternative', '[ɔːl\'tɜːrnətɪv]', 'adj.两者择一的；供选择的；非主流的 n.二者择一；供替代的选择', '1. We have the alternative plans of having a picnic or taking a boat trip. 我们在去野餐或者去乘船旅游两个计划中只能选一。 2. They are provided with the choice of two alternative flights. 有两个航班可供他们选择。 3. I\'d like to get some alternative music CDs for my niece. 我想买一些非主流的音乐唱片给我侄女。 4. I had no alternative but to accept the offer. 我除了接受该项提议之外，别无选择。', '副词: alternatively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sterile', '[\'sterəl]', 'adj.贫瘠的；无生气的；无生育能力的；无结果的；无菌的', '1. Sterile land does produce good crops. 贫瘠的土地也能出产优质的庄稼。 2. Mostly the mountains were still sterile. 大多数山仍然光秃秃的。 3. Their relationship had grown sterile over the years. 随着岁月的流逝，他们的关系变得了无生气。 4. Medical tests showed that he was sterile. 医学检查表明他没有生育能力。', '副词: sterilely 名词: sterileness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outfit', '[\'aʊtfɪt]', 'n.配备；用具；机构 vt.配备；供应 vi.得到装备', '1. She was prancing along in her new outfit. 她穿著全套新衣服神气活现地走著。 2. Such an outfit would be a useful addition to my wardrobe. 在我的服装中添置这一套会有用的。 3. The company will provide the sports outfits for all the players. 这家公司将为所有运动员提供全套运动服装。 4. His father bought a ski outfit for him on his birthday. 他父亲在他生日那天给他买了一套滑雪用具。 5. The mountain climbers were outfitted with the latest equipment. 登山者用最新的设备装备起来。 6. We will outfit two days before sailing. 我们将在出航前两天整装。', '名词: outfitter 过去式: outfitted 过去分词: outfitted 现在分词: outfitting 第三人称单数: outfits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('epic', '[\'epɪk]', 'n.史诗；叙事诗 adj.史诗的；叙事诗的；宏大的；壮丽的', '1. That movie was an epic about the Roman Empire. 那电影是一部有关罗马帝国的史诗般的作品。 2. The Odyssey is an epic of ancient Greece. 《奥德塞》是古希腊的一首史诗。 3. It is still the beginning of the home epic. 它依然是一篇家庭叙事诗的开端。 4. It is perhaps the best of epic fantasies. 这也许是史诗奇幻小说中最好的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ceramic', '[sə\'ræmɪk]', 'adj.陶器的 n.陶器；陶瓷学', '1. These ceramic tiles are the ultimate in modern kitchen design. 这种瓷砖是现代厨房装修中的极品。 2. There is a ceramic shop in the Arcade. 商店街中有一家陶器店。 3. I know a retired electrical engineer who has become a highly-paid ceramic artist. 我还认识一个退休的电力工程师，退休之后他成为了一名身价颇高的陶器艺术家。 4. There is a ceramic shop in the Arcade. 商店街中有一家陶器店。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bandit', '[\'bændɪt]', 'n.强盗；土匪', '1. She aimed a pistol at the bandit point-blank. 她用手枪直接瞄准强盗。 2. The sheriff snapped a shot at the fleeing bandit. 警长对逃跑中的强盗急速开了一枪。 3. If village has been infested bandit, You can know it. 如果村民成功抵御强盗的入侵，你也会得知这一消息。 4. The bandit chief has been hanged. 土匪头子已经被绞死。', '名词: banditry');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indignity', '[ɪn\'dɪɡnəti]', 'n.侮辱；轻蔑；有伤尊严', '1. She was subjected to indignity and humiliation. 她受到侮辱和羞辱。 2. The bandits subject us to all sort of indignity. 强盗们对我们加以各种侮辱。 3. They inflicted all kinds of indignities on their captives. 他们对俘虏百般侮辱。 4. This is the indignity for female. 这是对女性的侮辱.', '名词复数: indignities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sculpt', '[skʌlpt]', 'v.雕刻 n.雕刻；雕塑；雕刻品；雕塑品', '1. I\'ve ever had time to sculpt a bust of my father and to burnish it. 我甚至花时候雕了一尊我父亲的半身像，并把它擦得锃亮。 2. If I\'m trapped here. I could always sculpt a statue out of this beam! 如果我被困在这了，我可以常常用这个木梁刻雕像！ 3. The sculpt is so diaphanous. 这雕刻品造型挺别致，有点意思。', '过去式: sculpted 过去分词: sculpted 现在分词: sculpting 第三人称单数: sculpts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reside', '[rɪ\'zaɪd]', 'vi.居住；属于；存在', '1. This family has resided in this city for 60 years. 这个家族住在本城已有60年了。 2. They reside in a cottage at the foot of the mountain. 他们住在山脚下的一所小屋里。 3. The real power resides in the people. 真正的权力属于人民。 4. Memory has been shown to reside in some metals. 已经证实，记忆存在于某些金属中。', '名词: resider 过去式: resided 过去分词: resided 现在分词: residing 第三人称单数: resides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hormone', '[\'hɔːrmoʊn]', 'n.荷尔蒙；激素', '1. Ethylene is a growth hormone in plants. 乙烯是植物中一种生长荷尔蒙。 2. The hormone treatment might lead to the man growing breasts. 给男性注射许多的女性荷尔蒙可能导致他们长出乳房。 3. Estrogen hormone therapy advice is not yet uniform. 激素激素治疗意见尚不统一。 4. Emotional states can affect our hormone levels. 情绪会影响激素水平。', '形容词: hormonal 副词: hormonally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('groan', '[ɡroʊn]', 'v.呻吟；抱怨；发嘎吱声；受重压 n.呻吟；呻吟声', '1. The girl groaned in pain. 那女孩在痛苦中呻吟。 2. He was heard to groan. 有人听见他在呻吟。 3. Don\'t moan and groan because of a little setback. 不要受了一点挫折就唉声叹气。 4. The roof creaked and groaned under the weight of the snow. 屋顶被积雪压得发出吱吱嘎嘎的声响。 5. The wounded man uttered a groan. 那个受伤的人发出呻吟。', '副词: groaningly 名词: groaner 过去式: groaned 过去分词: groaned 现在分词: groaning 第三人称单数: groans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anxious', '[\'æŋkʃəs]', 'adj.渴望的；忧虑的', '1. The whole country was anxious for peace. 全国上下都渴望和平。 2. I am anxious to compare my fancy with reality. 我焦切地把我的想象同现实作一番比较。 3. Small businesses are anxious to experiment with computers. 小型企业都急于试用计算机。 4. She was anxious to enlighten me about the events that led up to the dispute. 她急着要使我明白引起这场争执的那些事情。', '副词: anxiously 名词: anxiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('protest', '[\'proʊtest]', 'n.抗议；反对 v.抗议；反对；申明；断言', '1. Half a million people held a mass protest against racism last night. 昨晚50万人举行了大规模的抗议活动反对种族歧视。 2. Some delegates walked out in a show of protest. 有几位代表退出会场以示抗议。 3. The minister resigned in protest against the decision. 这位部长为反对那项决策而辞职。 4. They protested to the mayor that the taxes were too high. 他们向市长提出抗议说税款过高。', '副词: protestingly 名词: protester 过去式: protested 过去分词: protested 现在分词: protesting 第三人称单数: protests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gender', '[\'dʒendər]', 'n.性；性别', '1. German has three genders. 德语中有三性。 2. The male and female genders are equal. 男性和女性是平等的。 3. Was it gender discrimination or were the female students simply superior writers? 是性别歧视还是女生天生就是擅长于写作呢? 4. Native English speakers are more gender blind when they mention their cousins. 在涉及表亲的时候,英语母语的人更容易混淆性别。', '形容词: genderless 过去式: gendered 过去分词: gendered 现在分词: gendering 第三人称单数: genders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('magnificent', '[mæɡ\'nɪfɪsnt]', 'adj.壮丽的；宏伟的；极好的', '1. The magnificent sights collect a jolly crowd. 壮丽的景色引来欢乐的人群。 2. The Hungarian view is magnificent from the summit of the mountains. 从群山之颠看到的匈牙利景色非常壮丽。 3. Just look at this magnificent autumn landscape! 看看这壮丽的秋景吧！ 4. The Taj Mahal is a magnificent building. 泰姬陵是一座宏伟的建筑。', '副词: magnificently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plight', '[plaɪt]', 'n.困境；苦境 n.誓约 vt.宣誓；订婚', '1. The Government seems to be closing its eyes to the plight of the unemployed. 政府似乎对失业者的困境熟视无睹。 2. The television pictures brought home to us all the plight of the refugees. 我们从电视上知道了难民所处的一切困境。 3. The plight of the refugees really wrung my heart. 难民处境惨苦真叫我牵肠割肚。 4. The plight of the refugees arouses the compassionate old man. 难民的困苦唤醒了那位有同情心的老人。 5. I plight that I will always be faithful to my work. 我发誓我会一直忠诚于我的工作。', '名词: plighter 过去式: plighted 过去分词: plighted 现在分词: plighting 第三人称单数: plights');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('soprano', '[sə\'prɑːnoʊ]', 'n.女高音；最高音部 adj.女高音的', '1. It\'s a soprano of great compass and of great purity. 这是一种音域宽广，高度纯正的女高音。 2. She sings in an exceptionally pure soprano. 她以异常纯美的高音歌唱。 3. She possesses a soprano voice of unusually fine quality. 她有着音质特别好的女高音歌喉。', '名词复数: sopranos');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deprive', '[dɪ\'praɪv]', 'vt.剥夺；失去；免职', '1. We have no right to deprive their life. 我们没有权利去剥夺它们的生命。 2. The spread of television have considerably deprive us of our time for reading. 电视的普及剥夺了我们相当多的阅读时间。 3. You can\'t deprive her of her rights. 你不能剥夺她的权利。 4. These trees deprive my house of light. 这些树遮住了我房屋的光线。', '形容词: deprivable 过去式: deprived 过去分词: deprived 现在分词: depriving 第三人称单数: deprives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('characterize', '[\'kærəktəraɪz]', 'vt.表示 ... 的典型；赋予 ... 特色', '1. The novelist characterizes his heroine as capricious and passionate. 这位小说家把女主人公刻画成变化无常而又多情的人。 2. He may be characterized as a man of hobbies. 他可以被称作是一个有癖好的人。 3. Your work is characterized by lack of attention to details. 你的工作特点是缺乏对细节的注意。 4. Bold outlines and warm colors characterize his dominate style in painting. 他大胆的绘画和所有的暖色调表现了他独有的绘画特色。', '名词: characterizer 过去式: characterized 过去分词: characterized 现在分词: characterizing 第三人称单数: characterizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bake', '[beɪk]', 'v.烤；烘焙；烘干；<非正式>灼热', '1. The bread is baking in the oven. 烤箱里正在烤面包。 2. I will bake Tracy several buns now. 我现在要为特蕾西烤几个小面包。 3. We bake bread and cake in an oven. 我们用烤箱烘面包与糕点。 4. In some places, bricks are still baked in the sun. 有些地方仍使用在太阳下晒干砖块的方法。', '过去式: baked 过去分词: baked 现在分词: baking 第三人称单数: bakes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fraud', '[frɔːd]', 'n.欺骗；诈欺；骗子', '1. She was put on trial for fraud. 她因涉及诈骗罪而受审。 2. Investigation of fraud was their commission. 调查诈欺舞弊是他们的任务。 3. He told people that he was a serious and well-known musician, but he was actually a fraud. 他告诉人们说他是一个严肃的著名音乐家,实际上却是个骗子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tower', '[\'taʊər]', 'n.塔；高楼 vi.高耸；胜过', '1. There is a sonorous bell in the tower. 塔里有一口洪亮的钟。 2. The tower was blown to atoms by the force of the explosion. 爆炸的力量把塔炸得粉碎。 3. The bell tower is the emblem of this city. 这座钟楼是这个城市的象征。 4. Above the victorian houses and shops tower the monster office blocks of the redeveloped center. 高耸于维多利亚时代房屋店铺之上的是新开发的市中心高大的办公楼群。', '过去式: towered 过去分词: towered 现在分词: towering 第三人称单数: towers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('director', '[də\'rektər]', 'n.董事；经理；导演；主管，总监；指挥者', '1. The board nominated him as the new director. 董事会指定他为新董事。 2. Her career culminated in her appointment as director. 她一生事业的顶峰是当上董事。 3. I wouldn\'t advise you to go against the director. 我反对你和经理对着干。 4. He has a lot of pull with the managing director. 他对总经理有很大的影响力。', '名词: directorship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('desirous', '[dɪ\'zaɪərəs]', 'adj.渴望的；想要的', '1. We are desirous of peace. 我们渴望和平。 2. Jane was desirous of meeting her mother . 珍渴望见到她的妈妈。 3. I am desirous to know further details. 我想要知道更多的细节。 4. She has always been desirous of fame. 她一直想成名。', '副词: desirously 名词: desirousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cue', '[kjuː]', 'n.暗示；提示；信号；（台球的）球杆 vt.给 ... 提示；把 ... 插入演出', '1. When I nod my head, that\'s your cue to interrupt the meeting. 我一点头，就是暗示你把会议中断。 2. The actor picked up his cue with effect. 演员对他所得到的提示迅速地作出了反应，效果良好。 3. The horses reacted as if on cue. 马像得了信号一样地起了反应。 4. Can you cue me when you want me to begin speaking? 你要我开始讲话时能给我暗示一下吗?', '过去式: cued 过去分词: cued 现在分词: cuing 第三人称单数: cues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('antibiotic', '[ˌæntibaɪ\'ɑːtɪk]', 'adj.抗菌的 n.抗生素', '1. Kimchi has antibiotic functions as lactic acid bacteria produced in the process of fermentation suppresses growth of harmful bacteria. 由于在发酵过程中产生的乳酸菌抑制了有害菌的生长，所以泡菜有抗生素作用。 2. When rhinosinusitis patients were not responsive to empiric antibiotic treatment in the Outpatient Clinic, specimens were taken from the middle meatus with cotton-tipped sticks. 在门诊中，当鼻腔鼻窦炎病患对抗生素治疗无效时，我们利用棉签从中鼻道取标本做嗜氧菌及厌氧菌的培养来决定正确的抗生素。 3. A new potent antibiotic will shortly be available. 一种新的高效抗生素不久将在市面销售。 4. She was injected with an antibiotic. 给她注射了抗生素。', '副词: antibiotically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scholar', '[\'skɑːlər]', 'n.学者；获奖学金的学生', '1. He is a complete scholar. 他是个无懈可击的学者。 2. He is not so much a writer as a scholar. 与其说他是作家倒不如说他是学者。 3. He ranks high as a scholar. 他是第一流的学者。 4. She impressed me as a scholar. 她给我留下了学者的印象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brag', '[bræɡ]', 'v.吹牛；自夸 n.大话；吹牛的人；傲慢的态度 adj.一流的；特别好的', '1. He used to brag that he would make lots of money. 他经常吹牛说自己会赚很多很多钱。 2. She bragged that she could run faster than I. 她夸口说她比我跑得快。 3. He often brag that how well he plays golf. 他常常自夸他高尔夫球打得如何如何好。 4. He made a great brag of his ability. 他夸耀自己的能力。', '比较级: bragger 最高级: braggest 名词: bragger 过去式: bragged 过去分词: bragged 现在分词: bragging 第三人称单数: brags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('readily', '[\'redɪli]', 'adv.容易地；迅速地；乐意地；欣然', '1. These problems are not readily soluble. 这些问题不容易解决。 2. They can readily be brought anywhere. 它们易于携带。 3. She stood up readily. 她迅速地站了起来。 4. She readily accepted his proposal of marriage. 她乐意地接受了他的求婚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complaint', '[kəm\'pleɪnt]', 'n.抱怨；疾病；诉苦；控告；投诉', '1. You have no cause for complaint. 你没有理由抱怨。 2. You\'re always having complaints. 你一直都有怨言。 3. I have a complaint of the chest. 我胸部不适。 4. She poured out her complaints before me. 她在我面前倾诉苦衷。', '动词: complain');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('substantiate', '[səb\'stænʃieɪt]', 'vt.证实；实体化', '1. The eyewitness can substantiate all the testimony. 目击证人能够证实所有的证词。 2. Despite this, more research is needed to substantiate this association. 尽管如此，这种联系还有赖更多研究来佐证。 3. Field experience did not usually substantiate the claims. 实际经验通常都不能使这些看法具体化。 4. This paper makes good use of modem technology to substantiate the idea. 这篇论文充分利用现代相关技术对这种设计思想加以具体化。', '名词: substantiation 过去式: substantiated 过去分词: substantiated 现在分词: substantiating 第三人称单数: substantiates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('butt', '[bʌt]', 'n.烟蒂；屁股；枪托 n.笑柄；靶垛 n.大酒桶 n.抵撞 v.插嘴；顶撞', '1. He stamped his butt on the floor. 他在地板上踩灭了他的烟蒂。 2. My sister says he has a hairy butt. 我姐姐说他屁股上长满了毛。 3. He was clubbed to death with a butt of a gun. 他是被人用枪托殴打致死的。 4. It was be a butt of the joke on my history. 这在我的历史中真是一个天大的笑柄。 5. The water butt catches the overflow from this pipe. 大水桶盛接管子里流出的东西。 6. He gave me a butt on the stomach. 他在我腹部撞了一下。 7. Don\'t butt in like that when I\'m speaking. 我讲话时别这样打断我的话。', '名词: butter 过去式: butted 过去分词: butted 现在分词: butting 第三人称单数: butts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rotate', '[\'roʊteɪt]', 'v.轮流；(使)旋转 adj.车轮状的', '1. The post of chairman rotates among members of the committee. 主席一职由委员会的成员轮流担任。 2. Interns have to rotate for a few months. 实习医生轮流工作了几个月。 3. He rotates the handle gently. 他轻轻地转动手柄。 4. Does the earth rotate on an axis? 地球是绕轴旋转的吗？', '形容词: rotatable 过去式: rotated 过去分词: rotated 现在分词: rotating 第三人称单数: rotates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plunge', '[plʌndʒ]', 'v.使投入；跳入；栽进；下降，急降，突降 n.投入；跳入', '1. She was about to plunge into something. 她就要采取什么行动了。 2. Don\'t plunge head first into another person\'s room. 别冒冒失失地撞进别人的房间。 3. The sudden jolt plunged her forward. 突然颠了一下，她向前打了个趔趄。 4. I waved my dog to plunge into the water. 我挥手示意我的狗跳入水中。 5. So why not take the plunge and have it over? 你为什么不鼓起勇气把这事赶紧解决了呢?', '过去式: plunged 过去分词: plunged 现在分词: plunging 第三人称单数: plunges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inform', '[ɪn\'fɔːrm]', 'v.通知；告诉；使熟悉；告发；赋特征于', '1. If you see something suspicious, inform the police at once. 你要是看到什么可疑的东西就马上通知警察。 2. I wasn\'t informed of the decision until it was too late. 等到我得知这项决定时,已经太迟了。 3. The UN Associations work to inform the public about the role the UN plays in global affairs. 联合国协会致力于使公众了解联合国在全球事务中发挥的作用。 4. The defendant informed against the other members of the ring. 被告检举犯罪集团的其他成员。', '过去式: informed 过去分词: informed 现在分词: informing 第三人称单数: informs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accuse', '[ə\'kjuːz]', 'v.谴责；控告；指责', '1. How dare you accuse me of lying! 你怎敢谴责我说谎! 2. We resolve not to accuse them to avoid troubles. 我们决定不起诉他们 3. I mustered up enough courage to accuse him. 我鼓起足够的勇气控告他。 4. He was accused of incompetence. 他被指责为不称职。', '副词: accusingly 名词: accuser 过去式: accused 过去分词: accused 现在分词: accusing 第三人称单数: accuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rehearse', '[rɪ\'hɜːrs]', 'vt.预演；排演；预先演习；详述；复述 vi.参加彩排', '1. In most cases, actors rehearse their parts. 在大多数情况下演员要预演他们的角色。 2. Our theatrical company will rehearse and stage a small theatre drama. 我们剧社将排演一出小剧场话剧。 3. They rehearsed how the United States would handle a hypothetical terroris t a ttack. 就美国将如何处理模拟的恐怖分子袭击 4. He rehearsed the events of the day. 他列举当天发生的事情。 5. They rehearse regularly and give periodic concerts. 他们定期排练', '名词: rehearser 过去式: rehearsed 过去分词: rehearsed 现在分词: rehearsing 第三人称单数: rehearses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('menace', '[\'menəs]', 'n.威胁；恐吓；<口>讨厌的人（物） v.威吓；威胁', '1. These weapons are a menace to world peace. 这些武器是对世界和平的威胁。 2. The man\'s lunatic behavior is a menace to society. 那个人的疯狂行为构成对社会的威胁。 3. That film creates an atmosphere of menace. 那部影片营造出吓人的气氛。 4. Your vicious dog is menacing my cat! 你那条恶狗对我家的猫太凶了！', '副词: menacingly 名词: menacer 过去式: menaced 过去分词: menaced 现在分词: menacing 第三人称单数: menaces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invoke', '[ɪn\'voʊk]', 'vt.援引；引起；求助；请求；乞灵于 [计算机] 调用.', '1. The government has invoked the official secret act in having the book banned. 政府援引国家机密保密法以禁该书。 2. It invokes new problems. 它引起一些新的问题。 3. The speech invoked his memory of childhood. 演讲唤起了他童年的记忆。 4. They invoked help in the desperate situation. 他们在走投无路的情况下恳求援助。 5. This command can invoke the applications. 这条命令可以调用应用程序。', '名词: invoker 过去式: invoked 过去分词: invoked 现在分词: invoking 第三人称单数: invokes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('simulate', '[\'sɪmjuleɪt]', 'vt.假装；模拟；模仿', '1. These insects can simulate dead leaves . 这些昆虫可以伪装成枯叶。 2. I tried to simulate surprise at the news. 听到这个消息后，我竭力装出一副吃惊的样子。 3. He shook a sheet of metal to simulate the noise of thunder. 他摇动一块金属薄片来模拟雷声。 4. You can simulate different browser types for tests. 您可以为测试模拟不同类型的浏览器。', '形容词: simulative 过去式: simulated 过去分词: simulated 现在分词: simulating 第三人称单数: simulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tube', '[tuːb]', 'n.管子；管状物；<英>地铁；电视；管状器官 v.提供或装上管子', '1. This tube is flexible but tough. 这管子柔软但很坚固。 2. She bought a tube of toothpaste. 她买了一管牙膏。 3. I go to work on the tube. 我经常乘地铁去上班。 4. What\'s on the tube? 电视上正演什么?', '过去式: tubed 过去分词: tubed 现在分词: tubing 第三人称单数: tubes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fixed', '[fɪkst]', 'adj.固定的；不变的；确定的 动词fix的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He received the fixed dole every month. 他每个月都能领到固定的救济金。 2. Fixed wages and lack of promotion act as a disincentive to employees. 工资固定又无晋升机会遏制了雇员的积极性。 3. He has a fixed pattern of behavior. 他有一套不变的行为方式。 4. He\'s a person with no fixed abode. 他是个居无定所的人。', '副词: fixedly 名词: fixedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('triangle', '[\'traɪæŋɡl]', 'n.三角(形)', '1. He outlined the triangle in red. 他用红笔画出三角形。 2. The angles of a triangle total 180. 三角形的三角之和等于180°。 3. The place is a cobbled triangle. 这个地方是一块铺石子的三角地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ornament', '[\'ɔːrnəmənt]', 'n.装饰；装饰物 vt.装饰', '1. The palace was rich in ornament. 宫廷装饰琳琅满目。 2. The clock is simply for ornament, it doesn\'t actually work. 那时钟纯粹是为了装饰,其实不能走。 3. There is an ornament made of shells on the wall. 墙上有一个贝壳做成的装饰品。 4. We bought some ornaments for the Christmas tree. 我们买了一些装饰品来点缀圣诞树。 5. I ornamented my room with flowers. 我用鲜花装饰房间。', '名词: ornamenter 过去式: ornamented 过去分词: ornamented 现在分词: ornamenting 第三人称单数: ornaments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('multiply', '[\'mʌltɪplaɪ]', 'vt.乘；增加 vi.做乘法；繁衍 adv.多样地；多重地', '1. If you multiply four by five, the answer is twenty. 四乘以五,答案是二十。 2. Let us multiply the height by the width to determine the area. 用宽乘以高来确定面积。 3. This will multiply our chances of success. 这将增加我们成功的机会。 4. He managed to multiply his profits. 他成功地增加了利润。 5. He learned to multiply at the age of five. 他五岁学会做乘法。', '过去式: multiplied 过去分词: multiplied 现在分词: multiplying 第三人称单数: multiplies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reconciliation', '[ˌrekənsɪli\'eɪʃn]', 'n.和解；调和', '1. The two sides come to reconciliation at last. 这两方最后讲和了。 2. He brought about reconciliation between former enemies. 他使旧时的仇敌和解了。 3. We\'ve tried our best to effect reconciliation between the two parties. 我们已尽了最大努力希望促成双方和解。 4. The key to reconciliation rests with them. 和解的关键在他们。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('integrate', '[\'ɪntɪɡreɪt]', 'v.整合；结合；取消隔离；求积分 adj.完整的；组合的', '1. The Message Board tool is an easy tool to integrate into daily school life. 留言板是一种非常方便的工具,可以将其整合到日常学校生活中。 2. Only 20% of teachers report feeling very well prepared to integrate education technology into classroom instruction. 仅有20%25的教师认为他们感觉能够将技术与课堂教学进行整合。 3. I learn quickly. I integrate disparate concepts with relative ease. 我学习速度很快,我能将完全不同的概念毫不费力地结合在一起。 4. We must carry out the Party\'s education policy that education should serve socialist modernization and the people and integrate itself with productive labor and social practice. 全面贯彻党的教育方针 5. Science is not an independent knowledge system, it has to integrate from various perspectives in order to reach a full understanding. 但是科学并非独立的知识系统，必须从不同的角度作综合性研究，方能对它有较完整的认识。', '形容词: integrative 过去式: integrated 过去分词: integrated 现在分词: integrating 第三人称单数: integrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jewelry', '[\'dʒuːəlrɪ]', 'n.珠宝；珠宝类', '1. This is a case with separate compartments for shoes, jewelry, etc. 这是一个分格存放鞋、珠宝等的箱子。 2. Jewelry and lace are mostly feminine belongings. 珠宝和蕾丝大多是女性用品。 3. I bought the watch at the jewelry counter. 这只表是我在珠宝柜买的。 4. The gang knocked over a jewelry store. 这伙歹徒抢劫了一家珠宝店。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tributary', '[\'trɪbjəteri]', 'adj.纳贡的；从属的；辅助的；支流的 n.支流；纳贡者；属国', '1. Sino-Siamese trade had two forms, tributary trade and civil trade. 中暹贸易主要分为两种形式：朝贡贸易与民间贸易。 2. Like Silla, Parhae was a tributary state of Tang-dynasty China. 如新罗一样，渤海国是中国唐朝的属国。 3. About half the 22 Ovimbundu chiefdoms were tributary to a larger chiefdom before Portuguese intervention in the 20th century. 在20世纪葡萄牙人实际占领之前，约有半数酋长领地臣服于一个大酋长。 4. The software of master station and tributary station are designed by VC ++ and configuration soft. 利用VC++和组态软件设计出了煤矿通风自动化系统的主站和分站软件。 5. This is a tributary of Zhujiang River. 这是珠江的一条支流。', '名词复数: tributaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maintain', '[meɪn\'teɪn]', 'vt.维持；维修；保养；坚持；断言', '1. It is absolutely vital that food supplies should be maintained. 维持食物的供给是绝对必要的。 2. They also help us to maintain the machinery. 他们还帮助我们维修机器。 3. They tell the peasants in detail how to maintain the pumps. 他们详细地教给农民怎样保养抽水机。 4. It is clearly illogical to maintain such a proposition. 坚持这种主张显然是没有道理的。', '形容词: maintainable 名词: maintainability 过去式: maintained 过去分词: maintained 现在分词: maintaining 第三人称单数: maintains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('motion', '[\'moʊʃn]', 'n.移动；动作；打手势；示意；提议；大便 v.示意；运动；向 ... 打手势', '1. The object is no longer in motion. 该物体已不处於运动状态. 2. Parts of the film were shown again in slow motion. 影片的一些部分以慢动作重放。 3. He made a motion with his hand to make me sit down. 他招手示意要我坐下。 4. His motion was rejected. 他的提议遭到了拒绝。 5. He opened the door and motioned me to come in. 他打开了门，招手让我进去。', '过去式: motioned 过去分词: motioned 现在分词: motioning 第三人称单数: motions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('notable', '[\'noʊtəbl]', 'adj.显著的；著名的 n.名人', '1. The difference contrast is notable. 差别对比是显著的。 2. This book had a notable impact on literature and art. 这本书对文学艺术产生显著的影响。 3. Tsim Sha Tsui is a notable tourist destination. 尖沙咀是著名的游客区。 4. You can also take in some of the notable architectural monuments. 你也可以将一些著名的纪念性建筑包括在参观的项目中。 5. He is the most notable son of Manchester. 他是曼切斯特最显赫的名人。', '副词: notably 名词: notableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tremor', '[\'tremər]', 'n.震动；颤动；战栗；兴奋；地震', '1. Her behavior caused a great tremor in the society. 她的行为引起当时社会的极大震动。 2. Others crowded behind him as a second violent tremor hit. 当第二次剧烈震动袭来时，他身后挤满了人。 3. There was a slight tremor in her voice. 她的嗓音里有些微颤动。 4. But the sudden tremor was more intense than any he had experienced. 但是这次突然颤动的力度却是前所未有的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('halt', '[hɔːlt]', 'n.停止；止步 v.停止；中止；暂停 v.踌躇；犹豫；跛行', '1. He tried to bring that debate to a halt. 他试图使这场辩论停止。 2. The officer called a halt to attacks. 那个军官下令停止进攻。 3. The thought brought her to an abrupt halt. 她一想到这个便猛地停下了。 4. No one can halt the advance of history. 谁也阻挡不了历史的前进。 5. He never halts in his speech. 他说话从不吞吞吐吐。', '过去式: halted 过去分词: halted 现在分词: halting 第三人称单数: halts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expedient', '[ɪk\'spiːdiənt]', 'adj.权宜的；有用的 n.权宜之计；临时手段', '1. Einstein found it expedient to use in the creation of his theories. 爱因斯坦发现这种本性在他理论的创建中是有用的。 2. It was expedient to retire gracefully. 体面的让步可算是权宜之计。 3. But that would be crassly expedient. 但那将是一个愚蠢的权宜之计。', '副词: expediently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fester', '[\'festər]', 'v.溃烂；化脓；恶化 n.脓疮；溃烂', '1. A dirty wound will probably fester. 一个弄脏了的伤口,可能会化脓。 2. It\'s lucky that the wound did not fester. 幸好伤口没有化脓。 3. The crisis will fester. 危机将会进一步恶化。 4. A broken bone can heal, but the wound a word opens can fester forever. 骨头断了可以治愈好，但是言语造成的伤害将会一直恶化下去。', '过去式: festered 过去分词: festered 现在分词: festering 第三人称单数: festers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('promote', '[prə\'moʊt]', 'vt.促进；提升；升迁；发起；促销，推销', '1. They discussed how to promote cooperation between the two countries. 他们讨论如何促进两国间的合作。 2. He has been promoted to general manager. 他已被提升为总经理。 3. He failed to get promoted for lack of resolution. 他因缺乏果断力而未能得到升迁。 4. He promoted a campaign to remind the public of protecting the wildlife. 他发起了一项旨在提醒人们保护野生动物的活动。', '形容词: promotable 名词: promotability 过去式: promoted 过去分词: promoted 现在分词: promoting 第三人称单数: promotes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shell', '[ʃel]', 'n.壳；炮弹；[计]外壳程序 v.脱落；去壳；拾贝壳；炮轰', '1. There is an ornament made of shells on the wall. 墙上有一个贝壳做成的装饰品。 2. All that remained of the building after the fire was an empty shell. 一场大火过后，这座建筑剩下的只是一个空壳。 3. The snail retreated into its shell. 蜗牛缩进壳里去了。 4. Shells were bursting all around. 炮弹在四处爆炸。 5. The wheat will shell after a few days. 麦子已熟透，再过几天就会脱落了。', '名词: sheller 过去式: shelled 过去分词: shelled 现在分词: shelling 第三人称单数: shells');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('specify', '[\'spesɪfaɪ]', 'v.详细说明；指定；阐述', '1. Please specify when you will be at home tomorrow. 请确切说明你明天何时会在家。 2. Also, you might have to specify the user name and password. 另外,您可能还需要指定用户名和密码。 3. Please specify the whole process of the project. 请阐述下这个项目的整个过程。', '名词: specifier 过去式: specified 过去分词: specified 现在分词: specifying 第三人称单数: specifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('archaeology', '[ˌɑːrki\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.考古学', '1. He displayed interest in archaeology. 他对考古学有兴趣。 2. She teaches archaeology at the university. 她在大学里教考古学。 3. The newspaper article waked my interest in archaeology. 报纸上的文章激起了我对考古学的兴趣。', '形容词: archaeological 异体字: archeology 名词: archaeologist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sporadic', '[spə\'rædɪk]', 'adj.不定时发生的；零星的', '1. Primary hepatic leiomyosarcoma is very rare with only sporadic cases reported. 摘要原发性肝脏平滑肌肉瘤非常少见，因此只有一些零星的病例报告。 2. Her only income came from sporadic leasing deals, forcing her to dip repeatedly into retirement savings. 她仅有的收入来自于零星的租赁交易，这令她不得不经常动用退休储蓄。', '副词: sporadically 异体字: sporadical 名词: sporadicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beneficial', '[ˌbenɪ\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.有利的；有益的', '1. It\'s a beneficial result to us. 对我们来说那是有利的结果。 2. Word of mouth advertising is the most beneficial. 口碑广告是最有利的。 3. Calcium is beneficial to our bones. 钙对我们的骨骼有益。 4. Fresh air is beneficial to our health. 新鲜空气有益于健康。', '副词: beneficially 名词: beneficialness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('descriptive', '[dɪ\'skrɪptɪv]', 'adj.描述的；叙述的', '1. The passage is purely descriptive. 这段文章完全是描述性的。 2. He told a very descriptive account of his journey. 他对旅行作了十分生动的叙述。 3. The report was so descriptive that I understood exactly. 这报道写得非常生动，我完全了解了。', '副词: descriptively 名词: descriptiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seismology', '[saɪz\'mɑːlədʒi]', 'n.地震学', '1. Historical seismology is a new developing subject. 中文摘要历史地震学是一门新兴的学科。 2. In pure seismology, the ground motion is generally expressed by its amplitude. 在纯粹地震学中，地面运动一般以振幅表示。', '形容词: seismologic 副词: seismologically 名词: seismologist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interrupt', '[ˌɪntə\'rʌpt]', 'v.打断；打扰；中断；阻碍 n.[计算机]中断', '1. It\'s not polite to interrupt a speaker. 打断人的谈话是不礼貌的。 2. The sudden noise from the next room interrupted my train of thinking. 从隔壁房间突然传来的吵闹声打断了我的思路。 3. I must go on, so please don\'t interrupt me. 我必须做下去,请不要打扰我。 4. Excuse me, I wonder if I could interrupt you for a moment. 对不起,能不能打扰您一会儿? 5. When I nod my head, that\'s your cue to interrupt the meeting. 我一点头，就是暗示你把会议中断。', '形容词: interruptible 名词: interruption 过去式: interrupted 过去分词: interrupted 现在分词: interrupting 第三人称单数: interrupts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gush', '[ɡʌʃ]', 'v.迸出；涌出；滔滔不绝地说 n.涌出', '1. Oil gushed out from the broken pipe. 油从断裂的管道中涌出。 2. A fountain of water gush from the break fire hydrant. 从损坏的消防栓里喷出水来。 3. In a moment more, the crowd began to gush forth from the doors of the church. 过了一会儿，人群便开始从教堂的大门蜂拥而出。 4. His words gushed out. 他的话滔滔不绝。 5. From the cellar grating floated up the flabby gush of porter. 隔着地窖的格子窗飘出走了气的黑啤酒味儿。', '过去式: gushed 过去分词: gushed 现在分词: gushing 第三人称单数: gushes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('economy', '[ɪ\'kɑːnəmi]', 'n.经济；节约 adj.经济的；廉价的', '1. The state of the economy is very worrying. 目前的经济状况令人十分担忧。 2. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 3. The last five years have seen a consistent improvement in the country\'s economy. 在最近的五年里，这个国家的经济状况一直在好转。 4. She preached economy as the best means of solving the crisis. 她大力鼓吹节约是解决危机的关键。 5. An economy class air ticket is fit for ordinary workers, because it costs much less. 经济舱机票对一般工作人员比较合适,因为它的价格要便宜得多。', '名词复数: economies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('continually', '[kən\'tɪnjuəli]', 'adv.不断地；频繁地', '1. His wife kept continually dinning in his ear. 他老婆不断地在他耳朵边唠叨个没完。 2. People legislate continually by means of talk. 人们用讲话不断地制订着法律。 3. He tried to enter it on the computer register, but he continually pushed the wrong keys. 他设法输入电脑记录，但频繁地敲错键盘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accidental', '[ˌæksɪ\'dentl]', 'adj. 意外的； 偶然的； 附属的 n. 偶然； 不重要的东西； <音>变调的临时符号', '1. Banging may also be accidental and painful. 这种撞击也可以是意外的及产生痛苦的。 2. He discovered an accidental error in his composition. 他在作文里发现了一个意外的错误。 3. Their marriage was quite accidental. 他们的结合是偶然的。 4. Your sin\'s not accidental, but a trade. 你的犯罪不是偶然的过失，你已经把它当作一件不足为奇的常事。 5. Their marriage was quite accidental. 他们的结合是偶然的。', '副词: accidentally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jeopardize', '[\'dʒepərdaɪz]', 'vt.危及；使处于危险境地；影响', '1. If you are rude to the boss, it may jeopardize your chance of success. 如果你对老板没有礼貌，那也许会危及你事业的成功。 2. Overworking can jeopardize your health. 工作过量可能会危及你的健康。 3. Being late so often will jeopardize your chances for promotion. 这么常迟到会危及你升迁的机会。 4. Soldiers jeopardize their lives in war. 士兵们在战争中使他们的生命陷入险境。', '过去式: jeopardized 过去分词: jeopardized 现在分词: jeopardizing 第三人称单数: jeopardizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('huddle', '[\'hʌdl]', 'n.杂乱一团；混乱；拥挤 v.推挤；乱堆；草率了事', '1. He shouted into the cavernous arena as if he were shouting into a huddle. 他对着球场吼叫，似乎他面对的是混乱的人群。 2. James insisted the Cavs needed to go bigger and broke from the huddle shaking his head in disagreement. 詹姆斯不住地摇头表示反对，他坚持认为骑士应该换上大个球员，打破场上的混乱局面。 3. The track led them to a huddle of barns and outbuildings. 那条路把他们带到了一片杂乱拥挤的谷仓和库房。 4. At the BeiBei plant, women huddle over a conveyor belt in frigid temperatures, gluing rubber sneakers together. 在贝贝公司，妇女拥挤在寒冷的传送带周围粘橡胶旅游鞋。', '名词: huddler 过去式: huddled 过去分词: huddled 现在分词: huddling 第三人称单数: huddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('asperse', '[ə\'spɜːs]', 'vt.洒圣水；诽谤', '1. He will adulate somebody in tne teeth and asperse him in the back. 他会当面吹捧一个人，背后又说他坏话。 2. \"To realize 4 modernization, wish to asperse warm blood and sweat. 为了实现四个现代化,愿洒热血和汗水。\" 3. Thank those who asperse you since it encouraged your personality. 感激中伤你的人，因为他砥砺了你的人格； 4. We enclose for realization draft asper the list at foot. 按照本函下列清单，附上应兑现的汇票。', '过去式: aspersed 过去分词: aspersed 现在分词: aspersing 第三人称单数: asperses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unearth', '[ʌn\'ɜːrθ]', 'v.发掘；掘出；发现并披露', '1. You will unearth a whole new history. 你们将会挖掘出一个完整的新历史。 2. They will unearth the buried treasure here. 他们将在这儿挖掘地下宝藏。 3. You may also unearth an ugly side of their personalities. 你会突然发现他们个性中让人讨厌的一面。 4. I\'ve asked Shirley to see what she can unearth on them. 我已经让雪莉去调查他们的情况了。', '过去式: unearthed 过去分词: unearthed 现在分词: unearthing 第三人称单数: unearths');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('personnel', '[ˌpɜːrsə\'nel]', 'n.职员；人事部门', '1. The personnel are not happy to change these rules. 全体工作人员对改变这些规定很不高兴。 2. The company\'s main problem is the shortage of skilled personnel. 这家公司的主要问题是缺少有技术的人员。 3. Army personnel are often forbidden to fraternize with the civilian population. 军职人员常被禁止与平民百姓友好往来。 4. Personnel is organizing the training of the new menbers of staff. 人事部门正在组织新雇员的培训。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('combustible', '[kəm\'bʌstəbl]', 'adj.易燃的；燃烧性的；易激动的 n.燃质物；可燃物', '1. Petrol is highly combustible. 汽油极易燃。 2. It was surrounded with heaps of combustible materials. 它周围是一堆堆易燃物资。 3. He has a combustible temperament. 他易冲动。 4. We must keep these combustibles away from the fire. 我们必须使这些易燃物远离火焰。', '副词: combustibly 名词: combustibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('giant', '[\'dʒaɪənt]', 'n.巨人；巨物；大公司 adj.巨大的', '1. The hero smote the giant with his sword. 英雄用剑猛劈巨人。 2. Shakespeare is a giant among writers. 莎士比亚是作家中的大文豪。 3. As we all know,Philips is the Dutch elctronics giant. 众所周知,飞利浦是荷兰电子业巨头。 4. That is one small step for a man, but one giant leap for mankind. 对于个人来说那是小小的一步,但对于整个人类来说却是一次巨大的飞越。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('polar', '[\'poʊlər]', 'adj.两极的；对立的 n.极线；极性', '1. Are there any animals in the polar circles? 南极圈和北极圈内有动物存在吗？ 2. The two systems of government are polar opposites. 这两种政体正好相反。 3. The two systems of government are polar opposites. 这两种政体正好相反。 4. Love and hatred are polar feelings. 爱与恨是完全相反的感情。 5. A molecule where the centers do not coincide is called a polar molecule. 正负电荷中心不重合的分子称为极性分子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inure', '[ɪ\'njʊr]', 'v.(使)习惯', '1. We should inure ourselves to hard life. 我们应该使自己习惯艰苦生活。 2. Yet this independence must not inure us to the awareness of the duties that constantly bind us to the past,present and future of humankind at large. 然而这种独立性绝不能让我们习惯于职责的意识，把我们束缚在人类的过去，现在和未来。', '名词: inurement');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('technological', '[ˌteknə\'lɒdʒɪkl]', 'adj.科技的；工艺的', '1. The cause of this is technological laziness. 这一现象的原因是科技的懒惰。 2. All these initiatives show that the Government has done a lot to promote technological development. 这些措施在显示，政府已做了不少功夫，致力促进科技的发展。 3. Technological progress has merely provided us with more efficient means for going backwards. 工艺的进步仅仅为我们的后退提供了更有效的工具。 4. In this paper, the comparison of technological production in polyoxyethglene fatty amine is discribed. 本文主要记叙述了聚氧乙烯脂肪胺两种生产工艺的比较。', '副词: technologically 异体字: technologic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pointed', '[\'pɔɪntɪd]', 'adj.尖的；尖锐的；直截了当的；有针对性的 动词point的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The ends were pointed and sharp as a knife. 两端尖尖的,像刀子一样锋利。 2. His daughter has a pointed nose. 他女儿长着一个尖鼻子。 3. They have narrow pointed leaves. 它们的叶子窄而尖。 4. The priests and rulers had listened in silence to Christ\'s pointed rebukes. 祭司和官长们沉默地听着基督尖锐的谴责,无言反驳。', '副词: pointedly 名词: pointedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fairly', '[\'ferli]', 'adv.公正地；相当地', '1. This company deals fairly with every client. 这家公司公正地对待每位客户。 2. I think I was quite fairly treated by the police. 我认为警察对我非常公正。 3. It\'s fairly hot today. 今天相当热。 4. His general state of health is fairly satisfactory. 他总的健康状况相当令人满意。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dwarf', '[dwɔːrf]', 'n.矮子；侏儒 vt.使矮小 vi.变小', '1. You are a giant of words and dwarf of action. 你是言词的巨人,行动的矮子。 2. There is a dwarf apple tree in our garden. 在我们的花园里有一棵矮苹果树。 3. The kind dwarf asked the little princess to have dinner with him. 善良的小矮人邀请小公主和他一起吃晚饭。 4. A dwarf on a giant\'s shoulders sees further of the two. 侏儒站在巨人肩上要比两个人看得远。 5. Each innovation destined to dwarf the extensive accomplishment of the Greeks-Euclidean geometry. 每一个创新都注定希腊人的巨大成就--欧几里德几何相形见绌。 6. They act out their dramas in a setting whose wilderness immensity both dwarf and ennobles whatever they achieve 他们在荒原上奠定了他们的事业，而广阔无际的天地既使他们的成就显得渺小，也显得崇高。', '形容词: dwarfish 名词: dwarfishness 名词复数: dwarfs 过去式: dwarfed 过去分词: dwarfed 现在分词: dwarfing 第三人称单数: dwarfs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pesticide', '[\'pestɪsaɪd]', 'n.杀虫剂；农药', '1. The crops are regularly sprayed with pesticide. 庄稼定期喷洒杀虫剂。 2. The insects have become resistant to the pesticide. 这些昆虫已经对杀虫剂有抗药性了。 3. The seeds and the pesticide are both ready. 种子跟农药都准备好了。 4. This pesticide is harmless to crops. 这种农药对农作物无害。', '形容词: pesticidal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obedience', '[ə\'biːdiəns]', 'n.服从；顺从', '1. The slaves gave passive obedience to their master. 奴隶们乖乖地服从他们的主人。 2. He demanded obedience from his inferiors. 他要求下级服从他。 3. He put up a token show of obedience. 他装出一副顺从的样子。 4. You are attracted to obedience and warmth. 你会被顺从和温暖的感觉所吸引。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cushion', '[\'kʊʃn]', 'n.垫子；橡皮软垫；缓冲 vt.加垫褥；放在垫子上；保护；减缓；为 ... 装垫子', '1. He covered the cushion with new material. 他给靠垫蒙上了新的料子。 2. She embroidered the cushion with flowers. 她把垫子绣上了花。 3. A hovercraft rides on a cushion of air. 气垫船悬浮在气垫上行驶. 4. The bush acted as a cushion to my fall. 这灌木在我摔下时起了缓冲作用。 5. We are going to cushion the rocking chair so that it is more comfortable. 我们要在摇椅上铺软垫，那么就会更舒适了。', '形容词: cushiony 过去式: cushioned 过去分词: cushioned 现在分词: cushioning 第三人称单数: cushions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('navy', '[\'neɪvi]', 'n.海军；船队；海军蓝', '1. He is a gunner of the British navy. 他是英国海军的一名炮手。 2. Beiyang Navy is the earliest naval force of China. 北洋水师是中国最早的海军部队。 3. The army, navy and airforce are all controlled by the Ministry of Defense. 陆海空军皆由国防部控制。 4. What I have said about the army also applies, mutatis mutandis, to the navy. 我谈到的陆军方面,如作适当变动,也适用于海军。', '名词复数: navies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fragile', '[\'frædʒl]', 'adj.易碎的；脆的；精细的；虚弱的', '1. Glasses are fragile and must be handled with great care. 玻璃制品易碎，必须小心轻放。 2. This glass plate is very fragile. 这个玻璃盘子很容易碎。 3. The fragile boxes arrived intact. 这些易碎的箱子完整无损地运到了。 4. Happiness is made of glass, it shines the brightest where it is most fragile. 幸福是玻璃做成的,它最脆弱的地方最闪亮!', '副词: fragilely 名词: fragility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plow', '[plau]', 'n.犁；耕地 vt.耕犁；费力通过；破浪前行 vi.耕田；费力前进；辛苦进行', '1. He teamed one horse and one cow to a plow. 他把一匹马和一头牛套在犁上。 2. The ground is apt for the plow . 这块地适于耕种。 3. The ground was plowed and planted with corn. 地翻耕后种上了玉米。 4. I plowed my way through the crowd. 我费力穿过人群。 5. This field plows easily. 这块田地容易耕。', '形容词: plowable 名词: plower 过去式: plowed/ploughed 过去分词: plowed/ploughed 现在分词: plowing/ploughing 第三人称单数: plows/ploughs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manner', '[\'mænər]', 'n.举止；礼貌；方式；习俗', '1. He is easy in conversation and graceful in manner. 他谈吐从容,举止优雅。 2. There is a noticeable coolness in his manner. 在他的举止中表现出一种明显的冷淡。 3. It is bad manners to interrupt. 打断别人说话是不礼貌的。 4. He often speaks in the most understated manner possible. 他说话尽可能保持低调。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('despicable', '[dɪ\'spɪkəbl]', 'adj.可鄙的；卑劣的', '1. Ingratitude is a despicable vice. 忘恩负义是可鄙的不道德行为。 2. It\'s despicable the way he treats those kids. 他对待那些孩子的方式是可鄙的。 3. It is despicable to desert your children. 你抛弃你的孩子是卑劣的。 4. Despicable as the fat restaurant detective was, his crime was less than theirs. 虽然那个饭店的胖侦探长行为卑劣，但他所犯的罪却要比他们的轻一些。', '副词: despicably 名词: despicableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('radioactive', '[\'reɪdioʊ\'æktɪv]', 'adj.放射性的', '1. Radioactive ray is material thing. 放射线是实际的物质。 2. Radium and uranium are radioactive elements. 镭和铀是放射性元素。 3. Radioactive waste must be stored on land. 有放射性的废物都必须存放在陆地上。', '副词: radioactively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stick', '[stɪk]', 'n.手杖；枝；杆 vt.刺入；插于；竖起 vi.钉住；坚持，遵守；粘贴；生效，起作用', '1. A walking stick is a must for me now. 如今我行走离不开手杖了。 2. We made the fire out of dry sticks. 我们用干柴枝来生火。 3. Hold the stick against crosswind. 向侧风方向压住杆。 4. A pin stuck me in the hand. 一根针刺入我的手。 5. Please help me to stick up the board on the big box. 请帮助我把木板钉在那个大木箱上。', '过去式: stuck 过去分词: stuck 现在分词: sticking 第三人称单数: sticks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hide', '[haɪd]', 'v.藏；隐瞒；遮避 vt.鞭打 n.兽皮', '1. I hid the broken plate behind the table. 我把打碎的盘子藏在餐桌后面了。 2. I hide the message in a cleave in the rock. 我把情报藏在石块的裂缝里。 3. She tried to hide her feelings. 她设法不表露自己的感情。 4. The future is hidden from us. 未来是我们难以预卜的。 5. The boots are made of buffalo hide. 这双靴子是由水牛皮制成的。', '过去式: hid 过去分词: hidden/hid 现在分词: hiding 第三人称单数: hides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('calculate', '[\'kælkjuleɪt]', 'v.计算；估计；考虑；推测；计划；指望', '1. I will calculate your bill for you. 我帮您计算账单。 2. Can you calculate the content of the tube? 你能计算出试管的容量吗? 3. Scientists have calculated that the world\'s population will double by the end of the century. 科学家已推算出世界人口在本世纪末将要增加一倍。 4. I calculate it\'s a waste of time to do that. 我想做那件事简直是在浪费时间。', '过去式: calculated 过去分词: calculated 现在分词: calculating 第三人称单数: calculates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tolerate', '[\'tɑːləreɪt]', 'vt.容许；忍受；容忍', '1. The school cannot tolerate cheating on exams. 该学校不容许在考试中有作弊现象。 2. We do not tolerate any form of discrimination. 我们绝不容许歧视的存在。 3. He can not tolerate the extremes of heat in the desert. 他忍受不住沙漠里的酷热。 4. I cannot tolerate your rudeness. 我无法忍受你的粗鲁。', '形容词: tolerative 名词: tolerator 过去式: tolerated 过去分词: tolerated 现在分词: tolerating 第三人称单数: tolerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stubborn', '[\'stʌbərn]', 'adj.顽固的；倔强的；难对付的', '1. That stubborn man always cleaves to his idea. 那固执的人不愿改变想法。 2. The child has a stubborn temper. 这个小孩脾气执拗。 3. This detergent can remove stubborn stains. 这种去污剂能去除难洗的污渍。 4. I have a stubborn cold and cough day and night. 我得了很难治的感冒，日夜咳嗽。', '副词: stubbornly 比较级: stubborner 最高级: stubbornest 名词: stubbornness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inferior', '[ɪn\'fɪriər]', 'adj.较低的；次等的；不如的；下级的 n.下级；属下；[印]下标符号', '1. These people occupy an inferior position in local society. 这些人在当地社会居于下等地位。 2. Captain is an inferior rank to major. 上尉是低于少校的一个官阶 3. A cheaper camera is not always inferior to a more expensive one. 廉价照相机的质量并总不比昂贵的差。 4. They never sell inferior goods. 他们从不销售次货。 5. A gentleman should always be civil, even to his inferiors. 有教养的人应该一直很有礼貌，甚至对待下属也一样。', '名词: inferiority');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beforehand', '[bɪ\'fɔːrhænd]', 'adv.预先；事先；提前', '1. I had made preparations beforehand. 我预先作了准备。 2. He warned me beforehand what to expect. 他预先提醒过我这件事。 3. We were aware of the problem beforehand. 我们事先就知道有这个问题。 4. Actually I meant to notify you beforehand. 实际上我是想事先通知你的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exponent', '[ɪk\'spoʊnənt]', 'n.【C】拥护者；说明者；楷模；指数', '1. Our senator is an exponent of free trade. 我们的参议员是一个自由贸易的拥护者 2. She\'s an exponent of the opinions of Freud. 她是弗洛伊德学说的鼓吹者。 3. Huxley was an exponent of Darwin\'s theory of evolution. 赫胥黎是达尔文进化论的解说者。 4. An exponent can be a person who pleads for a cause or an idea. 一位讲解者可以是为某种原因或者某种想法辩解的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('even', '[\'iːvn]', 'adj.平坦的；平和的；偶数的；相等的 adv.甚至；正当；更；恰好 v.使平坦；相等', '1. A billiard-table must be perfectly even. 台球桌必须十分平. 2. He spoke lightly in even tones. 他以平和的语调温和地讲话。 3. Cars with license plates ending in even numbers must go in this way. 牌照以偶数结尾的汽车必须走这条路。 4. He has an even chance of success. 他成败的机会参半。 5. He didn\'t even have the decency to show me the way. 他甚至连指点我路的礼貌也没有。 6. The path ran steeply up the hill and then evened out. 这条路很陡，到山上就平坦了。', '副词: evenly 名词: evener 过去式: evened 过去分词: evened 现在分词: evening 第三人称单数: evens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('controversy', '[\'kɒntrəˌvɜːsɪ]', 'n.争议；(公开的)争论', '1. The mayor will try to accord the controversy over the housing scheme. 市长试图调解住房规划方面的争议。 2. The remark touched off a heated controversy. 这句话引起了热烈的争论。 3. The new government appointments have caused much controversy. 政府在人事上作的新的委任，引起了许多争论。', '名词复数: controversies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('market', '[\'mɑːrkɪt]', 'n.市场；集市 v.销售；推销；买卖', '1. The market is rather depressed at the moment. 目前的市场相当萧条。 2. The sales manager wants to open up new markets in the Far East. 销售经理想在远东开辟新市场。 3. I bought a coconut in the market. 我在集市上买了一个椰子。 4. The inventor is trying to market his new product. 发明者正想销售他的新产品。', '过去式: marketed 过去分词: marketed 现在分词: marketing 第三人称单数: markets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subsidize', '[\'sʌbsɪdaɪz]', 'vt.给与补助金或奖助金；贿赂', '1. The government has refused to subsidize the car industry . 政府已拒绝给汽车工业补贴。 2. She\'s not prepared to subsidize his gambling any longer. 她再不愿意拿钱供他去赌博了。', '名词: subsidization 过去式: subsidized 过去分词: subsidized 现在分词: subsidizing 第三人称单数: subsidizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('licensed', '[\'laɪsnst]', 'adj.得到许可的 动词license的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. The restaurant is licensed for the sale of beer, but not wine. 这家餐馆领取的执照可出售啤酒，但不出售其它酒类。 2. It is always a good idea to sell through a licensed dealer. 通过特许经销商销售一直是个很不错的方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indifference', '[ɪn\'dɪfrəns]', 'n.不重视；无兴趣；漠不关心', '1. He treated my letter with indifference. 他不重视我的信件。 2. Doctrinal indifference is no solution to the problem of doctrinal differences. 教条化的不重视并非解决教条差异问题的良方。 3. He often treats me with indifference. 他对我常常漠不关心。 4. I feel let down by his indifference. 他的漠不关心使我感到失望。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('factious', '[\'fækʃəs]', 'adj.内讧的；闹派别的', '1. Fabvier was factious; Bavoux was revolutionary. 法布维埃是暴动分子，巴武是革命党人。 2. It is the most boring affair that have a factious life. 世上最累人的事,莫过于虚伪的过日子。 3. The factious dispute soon faded to historical insignficance. 那次宗派的争端很快成为历史上无足轻重的陈迹。 4. Tending to break up into parts or break away from a main body; factious. 有分裂倾向的倾向于分裂成几部分或从主体中分裂出去', '副词: factiously 名词: factiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('belittle', '[bɪ\'lɪtl]', 'vt.轻视；贬低；使相形见小', '1. He will no longer belittle me or interfere with my research. 他不再将轻视我或干涉我的研究。 2. But this is not to belittle the importance of ritualistic worship. 但这并不是轻视了仪式功修的重要性。 3. The Whigs may attempt to belittle our candidates. 辉格党人可能会试图贬低我们的候选人。 4. Don\'t belittle what he has achieved. 不要贬低他所取得的。', '名词: belittlement 过去式: belittled 过去分词: belittled 现在分词: belittling 第三人称单数: belittles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('encroach', '[ɪn\'kroʊtʃ]', 'v.侵占；侵犯；侵害', '1. His new house encroached on my land. 他的新房子侵占了我的土地。 2. I\'m sorry to encroach upon your time, but I really need your help. 抱歉，要来占用你的时间，可是我确实需要你的帮助。 3. The new law doesn\'t encroach upon the rights of the citizen. 新的法律没有侵犯公民的权益。 4. The army must never encroach upon the people\'s interests. 军队绝不能损害人民的利益。', '名词: encroacher 过去式: encroached 过去分词: encroached 现在分词: encroaching 第三人称单数: encroaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('survive', '[sər\'vaɪv]', 'vt.幸免于难；存活；艰难度过；比 ... 活得长 vi.活着；继续存在', '1. She was the only one to survive the crash. 她是这次飞机失事的唯一幸存者。 2. These birds are able to survive the perils of the Arctic winter. 这些鸟能在北极寒冷的冬天里生存。 3. I don\'t know how I ever survived high school. 我都不知道我是怎样熬过高中那段岁月的。 4. Santos is survived by his wife of 49 years. 桑托斯的妻子比他多活了49年。 5. You need to be tough to survive in the jungle. 要在丛林中活下来就要有坚忍不拔的意志。', '名词: survivor 过去式: survived 过去分词: survived 现在分词: surviving 第三人称单数: survives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slap', '[slæp]', 'n.侮辱；掴；拍击声 vt.侮辱；拍击；惩罚；申斥 adv.直接地；正面地；突然地', '1. It is a slap in the fame to call me a\'fat pig\'. 叫我“胖猪”是对我的侮辱。 2. It is a bit of a slap in the face when she refuseed to see me. 她拒绝见我，这简直是侮辱我。 3. He gave her a slap on the cheek and she began to cry. 他打了她一耳光，她就哭起来了。 4. He hit the water with a resounding slap. 他啪的一声拍了一下水。 5. You were slapping me just now. 你刚才正在侮辱我。 6. The thief ran slap into a policeman. 那贼与警察撞了一个满怀。', '名词: slapper 过去式: slapped 过去分词: slapped 现在分词: slapping 第三人称单数: slaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('faithful', '[\'feɪθfl]', 'adj.忠诚的；忠实的；忠贞的', '1. A true friend is faithful to the end. 真正的朋友到死都是忠诚的。 2. Mary is faithful to her husband. 玛丽忠实于她的丈夫。 3. His faithful pet dog bore him company. 他那忠实的爱犬给他做伴。 4. This newspaper gave a faithful account of the event. 这份报纸对那件事进行了如实的报道。', '副词: faithfully 名词: faithfulness 名词复数: faithful');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('patronage', '[\'pætrənɪdʒ]', 'n.赞助；光顾；任免权', '1. I am sorry to say that my patronage ends with this. 很抱歉，我的赞助只能到此为止。 2. The theatre is under the patronage of the art council. 那剧院得到了艺术委员会的赞助。 3. We respectfully solicit your continuous patronage. 恭请继续光顾。 4. Customer patronage, however, can be facilitated if there are similar stores in the same locale. 然而，如果在一个地方有一些类似的商店，顾客会更容易光顾。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expel', '[ɪk\'spel]', 'vt.驱逐；开除；排出', '1. Russia has lately decided to expel a US diplomat from its land, . 俄国最近驱逐了一名美国外交官。 2. He was expelled from the school. 他被学校开除了。 3. The headmaster decided to make an example of the pupil and expel him from the school. 校长决定开除该生以儆效尤。 4. The lungs expel carbon dioxide when we exhale. 当我们呼气时,肺所排出来的是二氧化碳。', '形容词: expellable 名词: expeller 过去式: expelled 过去分词: expelled 现在分词: expelling 第三人称单数: expels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('predator', '[\'predətər]', 'n.食肉动物；掠夺者；（动物的）捕食性天敌', '1. Young birds are very vulnerable to predators. 幼小的鸟易受食肉动物伤害。 2. The polar bear is the biggest land predator of them all. 顾名思义，北极熊的出产地为北极，是世界上体积最巨型的陆上食肉动物。 3. To Romanians, Russia is a predator. 而对罗马尼亚人而言，俄国人则是掠夺者。 4. Lion is a predator in the nature. 狮子是大自然中的掠夺者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deciduous', '[dɪ\'sɪdʒuəs]', 'adj.每年落叶的；非永久性的；（牙齿或角等）定期脱落的；蚂蚁交合后脱落翅膀', '1. Very few plants in my garden are deciduous. 我公园里的落叶植物很少。 2. The climate is not suitable for deciduous vegetation. 这种气候不适合落叶植物的生长。', '副词: deciduously 名词: deciduousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('destine', '[\'destɪn]', 'v.注定；指定；预定', '1. They were destined never to meet again. 命运注定他们永不再相逢。 2. Their attempt is destined to failure. 他们的企图注定要失败。 3. He was destined from his birth to enter into the church. 他生来就注定要当牧师。 4. They destinded him for the navy. 他们指定他去海军。', '过去式: destined 过去分词: destined 现在分词: destining 第三人称单数: destines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('save', '[seɪv]', 'v.救；节省；保存 n.救援，救助', '1. The doctor managed to save his life. 医生救了他的命。 2. Children should learn to save. 孩子们应学会储蓄。 3. I lent him my bike in order that he could save time. 我把自行车借给他,以便他能节省一些时间。 4. Save your strength for the hard work you\'ll have to do later. 留着点儿劲儿,你一会儿还得干重活儿呢。', '形容词: savable 名词: saver 过去式: saved 过去分词: saved 现在分词: saving 第三人称单数: saves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('Easter', '[\'iːstər]', 'n.复活节', '1. Christmas and Easter are Christian festivals. 圣诞节和复活节是基督教的节日。 2. Easter comes early this year. 今年复活节来得早。 3. At Easter, attendances at church rose. 复活节期间，到教堂做礼拜的人多了。 4. Each of my cousins received an Easter egg on Easter Day. 我的表兄弟们每人在复活节都得到了一枚复活节彩蛋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('auspicious', '[ɔː\'spɪʃəs]', 'adj.吉利的；幸运的；有利的', '1. The publication of my first book was an auspicious beginning of my career. 我的第一本书的出版是我事业吉祥的开始。 2. The new boy had an auspicious first day in the elementary school. 这个新来的男孩在小学校里有幸运的第一天。 3. Among historians of science, that\'s what is known as a rollicking and auspicious start. 在科学历史学家中，这就是所谓的快乐而幸运的开始。 4. The project had an auspicious beginning. 这个计划有一个良好的开端。', '副词: auspiciously 名词: auspiciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scenery', '[\'siːnəri]', 'n.风景；背景；布景', '1. The scenery is beautiful beyond description. 那里的风光美得难以描述。 2. We admired the splendor of the mountain scenery. 我们赞赏着壮丽的山景。 3. He asked us to lash the scenery up with rope. 他要我们用绳子把舞台背景绑起来。 4. The scenery in the play is beautiful, but the actors get in front of it. 那出戏的背景很美，可惜演员们站在前面给挡住了。', '名词复数: sceneries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('persuasive', '[pər\'sweɪsɪv]', 'adj.有说服力的；令人信服的', '1. He raised a persuasive argument. 他提出一个有说服力的论据。 2. She is really a persuasive supervisor. 她是个很有说服力的管理者。 3. We should at least be finding persuasive new ways. 我们至少应该找出能说服人的新办法来。 4. She went on with persuasive smoothness. 她用一种圆滑而娓娓动听的语调继续说下去。', '副词: persuasively 名词: persuasiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foil', '[fɔɪl]', 'n.钝头剑；箔；陪衬物；（击剑运动用的）花剑 vt.挫败；击退；阻挠', '1. The foil is a thrusting weapon with no cutting edge. 花剑，没有劈杀用的剑刀，是刺戳用兵器。 2. Our foil packets seal the flavour in. 我们用锡纸包装以保持原味。 3. Aluminum foil can be used for wrapping food. 铝箔用于包装食物。 4. This box of chocolate was wrapped round with foil. 这盒巧克力用箔纸包着。 5. Only confident, people will never foil. 只要有信心，人永远不会挫败。', '过去式: foiled 过去分词: foiled 现在分词: foiling 第三人称单数: foils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transaction', '[træn\'zækʃn]', 'n.交易；办理；处理；事务 （复）transactions: 学报；会报.', '1. Had you not helped us, we should have canceled this transaction. 假如没有你的帮助，这笔生意早就告吹了。 2. His failure in this transaction was due to nothing else than his own carelessness. 他在这笔交易中的失利完全是由于他自己的粗心大意。 3. Payments by cheque easily outnumbered cash transactions. 用支票付款在数量上大大超过现金交易。 4. They charge a fixed rate for each transaction. 他们对办理的每项业务收取一定的费用。', '形容词: transactional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('party', '[\'pɑːrti]', 'n.聚会；宴会；政党；一伙人；[律]当事人 vi.开派对', '1. It\'s a pity that you can\'t come to the party. 你不能来参加这次聚会，真可惜。 2. There was a liberal supply of drinks at the party. 那次宴会上有大量饮料供应。 3. The Labour party went out in 1980. 工党于1980年下野。 4. He was admitted to the Party last year. 他去年入党了。 5. That night we partied until dawn. 那晚我们痛饮到天亮', '名词复数: parties 过去式: partied 过去分词: partied 现在分词: partying 第三人称单数: parties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('keen', '[kiːn]', 'adj.敏锐的；强烈的；锋利的；热衷的；精明的', '1. The blind have a keen sense of touch. 盲人有敏锐的触觉。 2. Their keen eyes can penetrate the water to a depth of forty feet. 他们锐利的眼睛能透过水面看到40 英尺的深处。 3. Be brave, a fence between makes love more keen. 勇敢点,受到阻隔的爱情会更强烈。 4. The razor has a very keen edge. 这把剃刀有锋利的口。', '副词: keenly 比较级: keener 最高级: keenest 名词: keenness 过去式: keened 过去分词: keened 现在分词: keening 第三人称单数: keens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('principal', '[\'prɪnsəpl]', 'adj.主要的；首要的 n.本金；资本；校长；主角；委托人；主犯', '1. Our principal problem is lack of time. 我们的主要问题就是缺少时间。 2. My wages are the principal source of my income. 薪金是我收入的主要来源。 3. My principal concern is my family\'s welfare. 我至为关心的是我一家的幸福。 4. How much interest will there be on a principal of $5000? 5000美元本金的利息是多少？', '副词: principally 名词: principalship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spark', '[spɑːrk]', 'vi.闪烁；冒火花；热情回应 vt.激发；引起；向...求爱 n.火星；朝气；情人；俗丽的年轻人', '1. A tiny star can spark in the darkness. 小星星也会在黑暗中发光。 2. Druce lit the cigar, which began to spark and crackle. 德鲁斯点着一支雪茄，这支雪茄发出火花，噼噼啪啪地响起来。 3. He sparked to her plan. 他欣然同意了她的计划。 4. You can spark the spirit of enterprise. 你们可以激发事业上的进取心。 5. A cigarette spark started the fire. 香烟的火星引起这场火灾。', '名词: sparker 过去式: sparked 过去分词: sparked 现在分词: sparking 第三人称单数: sparks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deposit', '[dɪ\'pɑːzɪt]', 'v.放置；(使)沉淀；存储；付(订金等)；寄存 n.存款；定金；堆积物；矿床', '1. She deposited a pile of books on my desk. 她把一摞书放在我的书桌上。 2. Coarse crumb rubber is apt to deposit in asphalt. 粗的橡胶颗粒容易在沥青中沉淀。 3. The Nile floods the fields and deposits mud on them. 尼罗河泛滥，在田野上淤积一层泥。 4. He deposits a sum of money in the bank each month. 他每月在银行存一笔钱。 5. Ten yuan is the minimum initial deposit. 最低的开户存款金额是十元。', '名词: depositor 过去式: deposited 过去分词: deposited 现在分词: depositing 第三人称单数: deposits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('twist', '[twɪst]', 'v.缠绕；捻；搓；拧；扭曲 n.拧；捻；扭曲；盘旋；弯曲处', '1. She twisted the long scarf round her head. 她把那条长围巾围在头上。 2. Selecting the suitable twist factor in order to meet the needs of flax knitting yarn, it is the key to increase high_grade and productivity of flax knitting products. 选择合理的捻系数以满足针织用纱的要求是提高亚麻针织产品档次和生产效率的关键。 3. We twisted the bed sheets into a rope and escaped by climbing down it. 我们把床单搓成绳子，援绳下坠逃跑了。 4. The cap should twist off easily. 这个帽儿应该容易拧开。 5. She gave the lid another twist and it came off. 她又拧了一下，盖儿开了。', '形容词: twistable 副词: twistingly 名词: twistability 过去式: twisted 过去分词: twisted 现在分词: twisting 第三人称单数: twists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('creativity', '[ˌkriːeɪ\'tɪvəti]', 'n.创造力；创造', '1. This toy will help children with their creativity. 这种玩具有助于孩子们的创造力。 2. Creativity is the lifeblood of a service economy. 创意是服务型经济的命脉。 3. Asking questions often generates the spark of creativity. 提问常常会引发创造的火花。 4. Creativity is allowing yourself to make mistakes. Art is knowing which ones to keep. 搞创造允许犯错。搞艺术应知取舍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mammoth', '[\'mæməθ]', 'adj.巨大的；庞大的 n.长毛象；猛犸', '1. Building the new railroad will be a mammoth job. 修建那条新铁路将是一项巨大工程。 2. The mammoth buffalo roamed the plains. 庞大的野牛群出没在这些平原上。 3. By comparison, the Great Wall in China is a mammoth presence. 相比之下，中国的长城真是个庞然大物。 4. The woolly mammoth was a month old when she died. 这只长毛象刚满月就不幸身亡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mechanism', '[\'mekənɪzəm]', 'n.机制；原理 n.结构；机构；机械装置', '1. The WTO provides a mechanism for resolving trade disputes. 世贸组织提供了一种解决贸易争端的机制。 2. The acting mechanism of coating mist polycoagulant is introduced. 介绍了漆雾凝聚剂的作用原理及选择漆雾凝聚剂的方法。 3. Analyzing the velocity and acceleration of the follower based on the Assur-group method and the inversion of the mechanism. 以杆组分析方法为基础，结合转化机构原理及凸轮机构的相对速度理论进行从动件的速度和加速度分析。 4. She studied the mechanisms of the body. 她研究身体的结构。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('minimum', '[\'mɪnɪməm]', 'adj.最少的；最低程度的 n.最低限度；最小量', '1. That is the minimum number necessary to complete the circuit. 这是完善循环的最低限度人数。 2. The minimum wage is 4.25 dollars an hour. 最低工价为每小时四点二五美元。 3. Repairing your car will cost a minimum of 100 dollars. 修理你的汽车最低限度要100美元。 4. The class needs a minimum of 6 pupils to continue. 这个班最低限度要六个学生才可以继续办下去。', '名词复数: minimums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('motivate', '[\'moʊtɪveɪt]', 'vt.激发(兴趣或欲望)；给与动机', '1. He is just sitting there doing nothing. He needs to be motivated. 他坐在那儿什么也不干,他需要一点动力去激发他。 2. The crime appears to have been motivated by hatred. 犯罪似乎都来自于仇恨。 3. A good teacher is one who can motivate his students. 好老师是能激励学生的老师。', '名词: motivator 过去式: motivated 过去分词: motivated 现在分词: motivating 第三人称单数: motivates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('doubtful', '[\'daʊtfl]', 'adj.可疑的；怀疑的；不确定的', '1. It is doubtful whether it is true or not. 这件事的真假是可疑的。 2. The fact that he won the first place is doubtful. 他得了第一名是让人可疑的。 3. He is an author of doubtful reputation. 他是一位名声不太好的作家。 4. The ethics of his decision are doubtful. 他的这一决定是否合乎道德规范值得怀疑。', '副词: doubtfully 名词: doubtfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('companion', '[kəm\'pæniən]', 'n.同伴；志趣相投的人；成对物品之一；参考书 v.陪伴', '1. He is a good companion on the journey. 他是个好旅伴。 2. He had always considered her an ideal companion for his son. 他一直以为她是他儿子的理想伴侣。 3. The dog has been her constant companion these past ten years. 过去十年来,这只狗一直与她形影不离。 4. His brother is not much of a companion for him. 他兄弟与他情趣不甚相投。 5. I worked as a companion to an old princess. 我当过一位老公爵夫人的陪伴人。', '过去式: companioned 过去分词: companioned 现在分词: companioning 第三人称单数: companions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contaminate', '[kən\'tæməˌneɪt]', 'vt.弄脏；污染', '1. Contaminate your bed, and you will one night suffocate in your own waste. 如果你弄脏了自己的环境，总有一天会窒息在你所丢弃的垃圾之中。 2. All over the world, oil spills regularly contaminate coasts. 在世界各地，油溢出物经常污染着海岸。 3. They are contaminating the minds of our young people with these subversive ideas. 他们这些颠覆性的思想是对我们年轻人的精神污染。', '形容词: contaminative 名词: contaminator 过去式: contaminated 过去分词: contaminated 现在分词: contaminating 第三人称单数: contaminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cereal', '[\'sɪriəl]', 'n.麦片粥；谷类食物 adj.谷类的；谷物的', '1. He sprinkled sugar over his cereal. 他在麦片粥里撒上了糖。 2. I have a bowl of cereal every morning. 我每天早晨吃一碗麦片粥。 3. The breakfast cereal is enriched with vitamins. 维生素增加了早餐谷类食物的营养价值。 4. The disease attacks cereal crop. 这种疾病侵害了谷类作物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('criterion', '[kraɪ\'tɪriən]', 'n.标准；准则', '1. Practice is the sole criterion for testing truth. 实践是检验真理的唯一标准。 2. He thinks that the criterion of success is the ability to work joyfully. 他认为成功的检验标准是看能否愉快地生活。 3. We have a clear-cut criterion to go by. 我们有个可供遵循的明确标准。 4. The table shows the scoring for each criterion and criterion group. 上表显示每一准则和准则组别的评分。', '形容词: criterial 名词复数: criteria');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relinquish', '[rɪ\'lɪŋkwɪʃ]', 'vt.放弃；放手', '1. I had relinquished all hopes that she was alive. 我已经放弃了她还活着的一切希望。 2. Finally he relinquished his plan for want of business. 因生意需要他只好放弃计划。 3. He relinquished his share to his partner. 他把他的股权让给了他的合伙人。 4. She relinquished possession of the house to her sister. 她把房子的所有权让给了她妹妹。', '名词: relinquisher 过去式: relinquished 过去分词: relinquished 现在分词: relinquishing 第三人称单数: relinquishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('whir', '[wɜːr]', 'v.作呼呼声；发飕飕声的飞或转 n.呼呼声；飕飕声 =whirr.', '1. The bird flew past, its wings whirring. 那只鸟飞了过去，翅膀发出呼呼的声音。 2. A limousine whirred him away. 一辆轿车呼地一声把他载走。 3. There was a sudden whir as the airplane started its engines. 飞机的发动机起动时，立即发出呼呼的声响。 4. Only the whir of the air conditioner broke the silence in the office 打破办公室内寂静的，只有空气调节机呼呼的转动声。', '过去式: whirred 过去分词: whirred 现在分词: whirring 第三人称单数: whirs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hominid', '[\'hɑːmɪnɪd]', 'n.原始人类 adj.灵长类的', '1. The several branches of early hominid were not immune to the changes in climate. 早期人科动物的不同分支在气候变化中也未能幸免。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thaw', '[θɔː]', 'n.融雪 v.使融解；暖和', '1. This year the thaw will set in early. 今年融雪将提早。 2. The sky, swollen with the clouds that announce a thaw, hung as low as before a summer storm. 天上涨满了预告融雪的云，直压到人头顶上，像夏天里暴风雨之前一样。 3. Come up to the fire,and you will thaw out. 到火炉边来，你就会觉得暖和。 4. This warm weather should thaw the ice on the road very quickly. 这样暖和的天气可以使路上的冰很快地融化。', '过去式: thawed 过去分词: thawed 现在分词: thawing 第三人称单数: thaws');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('burrow', '[\'bɜːroʊ]', 'n.(兔子等)所掘的地洞 vt.挖掘(洞穴)；钻进 vi.翻寻；挖洞', '1. The ideal riverbank is crumbly enough for the birds to excavate a nesting burrow with their beaks. 理想的河岸边土壤很松软，这些鸟可以很轻松的用自己喙去凿出适合做窝的地洞。 2. You burrow and rankle in his heart! 你挖掘并折磨他的心灵！ 3. Burrow beneath laudatory headlines on business and political leaders, and it becomes clear that the strategy works. 挖掘赞誉标题背后的商政要人，这个策略已变得有效。 4. Nobody comes to visit me, although a mouse did burrow into my cabin once. 没有人来拜访我，不过确实有一只耗子曾挖洞来过我的小木屋。', '名词: burrower 过去式: burrowed 过去分词: burrowed 现在分词: burrowing 第三人称单数: burrows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dingy', '[\'dɪndʒi]', 'adj.肮脏的；昏暗的', '1. He lives in a dingy room. 他住在一个肮脏的屋子里。 2. His office is really dark and dingy . 他的办公室实在是又暗又脏。 3. It was a rather dingy night, although a fair number of stars were out. 这是个昏暗的夜晚，虽然天空中有相当数量的星星。', '副词: dingily 比较级: dingier 最高级: dingiest 名词: dinginess');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cathedral', '[kə\'θiːdrəl]', 'n.大教堂', '1. Photography is strictly forbidden in the cathedral. 教堂内严禁摄影。 2. This street offers a fine vista of the cathedral. 这条街的尽头是个大教堂，远远望去非常好看。 3. The dome of St. Paul Cathedral is well known in the world. 圣保罗教堂的圆顶闻名于世。 4. This cathedral was regarded as a miracle in architectural history. 这座大教堂被认为是建筑史上的奇迹。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inanity', '[ɪ\'nænəti]', 'n.空虚；愚蠢；空洞的言行', '1. I laugh all alone at my complete inanity. 十分空虚时,我就独自大笑。 2. I was amazed at the inanity of some of her comments. 我惊讶于她一些愚蠢的评论。 3. Their statement was a downright inanity. 他们的声明是彻头彻尾的废话。', '名词复数: inanities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concoct', '[kən\'kɑːkt]', 'v.捏造；调制', '1. And they had taken me so long to concoct. 我花了好长时间编造这些谎言。 2. She\'d concocted some unlikely tale about the train being cancelled. 她胡编了一通瞎话,说什么那班火车给取消了。 3. I gave her a tip on how to concoct a new kind of soup. 我教她配制一种新汤的诀窍。', '名词: concocter 过去式: concocted 过去分词: concocted 现在分词: concocting 第三人称单数: concocts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dogma', '[\'dɔːɡmə]', 'n.教条；教义；信条', '1. Beliefs have ossified into rigid dogma. 信仰已僵化为不可更动的教条。 2. He conquered the old code and the old dogma. 他战胜了陈旧的秩序和陈旧的教条。 3. The Catholic dogma was to her nothing more than a set of rules. 天主教的教义对她只是一套清规戒律罢了。 4. The newspaper seeks to be independent of political dogma. 这份报纸力求不受政治信条影响。', '名词复数: dogmas');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dignity', '[\'dɪɡnəti]', 'n.尊严；高贵；端庄', '1. He would do nothing beneath his dignity. 他决不愿意干任何有损自身尊严的事。 2. The real dignity of a man lies in what he is, not in what he has. 一个人的真正尊严在于他的品格，而非他的财富。 3. A man\'s dignity depends not upon his wealth but upon his character. 人高尚与否不取决於他的财富,而取决於他的品格。 4. She bears herself with dignity. 她举止庄重大方。', '名词复数: dignities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('site', '[saɪt]', 'n.地点；位置；现场 vt.使 ... 位于', '1. That sale precludes further development on this site. 卖出以后妨碍了这一地点的进一步发展。 2. The site is being developed by a London property company. 这块地正在由伦敦的一家地产公司开发利用。 3. Excavation of the site will begin tomorrow. 明天开始挖掘工作。 4. The house is built on the site of a medieval prison. 这个房屋建立在中世纪监狱的位置。 5. Is it safe to site the power station here? 在这建造发电厂安全吗？', '过去式: sited 过去分词: sited 现在分词: siting 第三人称单数: sites');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quaint', '[kweɪnt]', 'adj.离奇有趣的；古色古香的；古怪的', '1. Old photographs seem quaint to us today. 旧照片现在就我们来看来似乎古怪有趣。 2. The meadow and brook are quaint. 草地和小河很有趣。 3. Grandma lives in a quaint old cottage. 奶奶住在一栋古色古香的乡间别墅里。 4. Our neighbor is a quaint old lady. 我们的邻居是位古怪的老太太。', '副词: quaintly 比较级: quainter 最高级: quaintest 名词: quaintness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('congested', '[kən\'dʒestɪd]', 'adj.拥挤的；堵塞的；充血的；鼻子不通的 动词congest的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The street was congested with traffic. 街道因往来车辆而阻塞。 2. He had a cold and was very congested. 他患了感冒，鼻子不通。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chill', '[tʃɪl]', 'v.(使)变冷；(使)扫兴；[冶]冷淬 n.寒冷；扫兴；寒心；着凉 adj.冷淡的；寒冷的', '1. Come by the fire you must be chilled to the marrow! 到火旁边来吧－－你一定冻坏了。 2. The night air chilled his bones. 夜间的寒气使他感到冰冷彻骨。 3. The raw weather chilled our enthusiasm for a swim. 天气阴冷，我们游泳的兴致大减。 4. There was a chill in the air this morning. 今天早上有点冷冰冰的。 5. The host gave him a chill reception. 主人(对客人而言)对他的接待是冷淡的。', '副词: chillingly 名词: chillness 过去式: chilled 过去分词: chilled 现在分词: chilling 第三人称单数: chills');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allocate', '[\'æləkeɪt]', 'vt.分派；分配；分配额', '1. The system was unable to allocate a new data object. 系统无法分派新的数据对象。 2. Allocate rations for a week - long campingtrip. 分配一星期外出野营的定额。 3. You must allocate the money carefully. 你们必须谨慎地分配钱。', '形容词: allocable 名词: allocation 过去式: allocated 过去分词: allocated 现在分词: allocating 第三人称单数: allocates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convenient', '[kən\'viːnjənt]', 'adj.便利的；方便的', '1. Internet makes it convenient for us to get in touch with each other. 互联网使得我们相互联系便利了。 2. Please come whenever it is convenient to you. 方便的时候,请随时来。', '副词: conveniently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commodious', '[kə\'moʊdiəs]', 'adj.宽敞的', '1. It is a commodious house. 这是一间宽敞的房屋。 2. The students\' cupboards are very commodious. 学生们的橱柜非常宽敞。', '副词: commodiously 名词: commodiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evolutionary', '[ˌiːvə\'luːʃəneri]', 'adj.进化的；发展的；演变的', '1. The facts are interpreted in the light of evolutionary faith. 这些事实被按照进化的理念来解释。 2. It is a natural evolutionary cycle where the energy will be redistributed. 它是一个能量将被重新分配的自然进化的周期。 3. Offshore investing can be an evolutionary process. 离岸投资是个不断发展的过程。 4. The emergence of this field has been profoundly influenced by the progress in reconfigurable hardware and evolutionary computation. 这个领域的出现已经深地在再组合的硬体和进化的计算内受了发展的影响。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infect', '[ɪn\'fekt]', 'vt.传染；感染', '1. The open wound soon became infected. 裸露的伤口很快就受到了感染。 2. The flu virus infected almost the entire class. 全班几乎人人都染上了流行性感冒病毒。 3. There is a virus that infects word-processing documents recently. 最近有种病毒专门传染WORD文件。 4. Her cheerful spirits and bubble laughter infect the whole class. 她那快乐的情绪和爽朗的笑声感染了全班。', '过去式: infected 过去分词: infected 现在分词: infecting 第三人称单数: infects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abandon', '[ə\'bændən]', 'v.放弃；抛弃；放纵 n.放纵', '1. Those who abandon themselves to despair can not succeed. 那些自暴自弃的人无法成功。 2. Despite some difficulties, they\'re not going to abandon the plan. 尽管他们遇到了一些困难,但并不打算放弃这个计划。 3. The cruel man abandoned his wife and child. 那个狠心的男人抛弃了他的妻儿。 4. They abandon themselves to drinking. 他们沉湎于饮酒。 5. He signed cheques with careless abandon. 他无所顾忌地乱开支票。', '名词: abandonment 过去式: abandoned 过去分词: abandoned 现在分词: abandoning 第三人称单数: abandons');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('external', '[ɪk\'stɜːrnl]', 'adj.外来的；外部的；外面的；表面的 n.外观；外部；外界事物', '1. This news program only covers external events. 这一新闻节目只报道国外消息。 2. The external sector performance also improved significantly during the period. 在此期间,我国的涉外经济成绩斐然。 3. This force takes two forms, one internal and one external. 这个权力有两种形式:一种是对内的,一种是对外的。 4. All his injuries are external. 他受的伤都是外伤。 5. The external features of the building are very attractive. 这座建筑物的外观是很吸引人的。', '副词: externally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('significant', '[sɪɡ\'nɪfɪkənt]', 'adj.重要的；有意义的；意味深长的；显著的', '1. The question under discussion is significant. 讨论中的问题是重要的。 2. Economic conditions are significant in many ways. 经济条件在许多方面都是很重要的。 3. All of us want our lives to be significant. 我们每个人都希望我们的人生是有意义的。 4. It was truly a significant conversation. 这是非常有意义的谈话。', '副词: significantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impetus', '[\'ɪmpɪtəs]', 'n.推动力；刺激', '1. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。 2. The present conflict may provide fresh impetus for peace talk. 目前的冲突可能会给和谈提供新的推动力。 3. Her speech gave an impetus to my ideas. 她的讲话激发了我的思绪。 4. His articles provided the main impetus for change. 他的那些文章是促进变革的主要推动力。', '名词复数: impetuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tag', '[tæɡ]', 'n.标签；附属物；捉人游戏；谚语；名称 vt.连接；附以签条；尾随；添饰；指责 vi.紧随；尾随', '1. She peered at the tag to read the price. 她细看标签以看清价格。 2. The kids are playing tag over there. 小孩子正在那儿玩捉人游戏。 3. He would make a shot at a Latin tag. 他要尝试一下拉丁文短语。 4. A tag is another name for a media information attribute. 标记是媒体信息属性的另一个名称。 5. Will you tag these two together? 你把这两个连接在一起好吗? 6. If you\'re going to the cinema, do you mind if I tag along ? 你要是去看电影, 我也一起去行吗?', '过去式: tagged 过去分词: tagged 现在分词: tagging 第三人称单数: tags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quantify', '[\'kwɑːntɪfaɪ]', 'v.用数量表示；量化', '1. The cost of the flood damage is impossible to quantify. 这次水灾的损失是无可估量的。 2. Now, a new study has helped quantify this trend. 现在有一项新的研究对这一趋势进行了量化。 3. It\'s difficult to quantify the value of space exploration. 把太空探索的价值进行量化是很困难的。', '形容词: quantifiable 名词: quantification 过去式: quantified 过去分词: quantified 现在分词: quantifying 第三人称单数: quantifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('schedule', '[\'skedʒuːl]', 'n.时间表，日程；一览表；计划 v.预定；安排；编制目录', '1. I\'ll work out the schedule. 我来拟定时间表。 2. Please show me the taxation schedule. 请让我看看税收一览表。 3. Owing to various delays en route, we arrived two days behind schedule. 由于路上的种种耽搁, 我们比原计划迟到了两天。 4. He was scheduled to attend the party. 他预定出席那个宴会。', '形容词: schedular 名词: scheduler 过去式: scheduled 过去分词: scheduled 现在分词: scheduling 第三人称单数: schedules');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elm', '[elm]', 'n.榆树；榆木', '1. We planted some elms in the yard. 我们在院子里种了一些榆树。 2. The farmhouse is dignified by the great elm around it. 这家农舍由于周围的大榆树而增光不少。 3. They have lopped away the biggest of the branches of that elm overhanging the road. 他们把那棵榆树低垂在公路上的最大的枝子砍掉了。 4. Water pipes used to be made out of elm. 水管过去是用榆木做的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sly', '[slaɪ]', 'adj.狡猾的；会心的；淘气的；诡异的', '1. She\'s a sly puss. 她是个刁滑的姑娘。 2. The sly fox nimbly eluded the dogs. 那只狡猾的狐狸灵活地躲避开那群狗。 3. He cast a sly glance at his bridge partner. 他向桥牌搭档使了个会意的眼色。 4. The sly cat stole the meat while the cook\'s back was turned. 淘气的猫趁厨师转身之机偷吃了肉。', '副词: slyly 比较级: slier/slyer 最高级: sliest/slyest 名词: slyness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('domineering', '[ˌdɑːmə\'nɪrɪŋ]', 'adj.专横的；作威作福的', '1. He is a domineering sort of fellow. 他是一个飞扬跋扈的人。 2. He was brought up by a cold and domineering father. 他是由冷酷而专横的父亲抚养成人的。 3. That domineering manner of yours cuts no ice here with me. 你那种盛气凌人的态度在这里对我不起作用。 4. She has at last come into her own since her domineering sister left home. 自从她那指手划脚的姐姐离开家庭之后，她终于可以自己作主了。', '副词: domineeringly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incapacitate', '[ˌɪnkə\'pæsɪteɪt]', 'v.使不能；使不适于', '1. A device or substance, such as tear gas, used to incapacitate individuals temporarily, as in riot control. 致残剂一种可使人暂时致残的装置或物质，如平定暴乱时所用的催泪瓦斯', '名词: incapacitation 过去式: incapacitated 过去分词: incapacitated 现在分词: incapacitating 第三人称单数: incapacitates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hypothesize', '[haɪ\'pɑːθəsaɪz]', 'v.假设；假定；猜测', '1. Some of the archaeologists mistakenly hypothesize that the body is missing because human sacrifice was involved. 某些考古学家错误地假设身体是不完整的，因为人是牺牲。 2. That finding led researchers to hypothesize that caffeine may increase the risk of breast cancer. 该发现引导研究者假设咖啡因增加乳腺癌发生风险。 3. Similarly, one might also hypothesize that females, on the other hand, select toys that allow them to hone the skills they will one day need to nurture their young. 同样地，我们也可以假定，雌性选择的玩具，可以让她们磨练照顾孩子的技巧，反正她们迟早会生养子女。', '过去式: hypothesized 过去分词: hypothesized 现在分词: hypothesizing 第三人称单数: hypothesizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jeans', '[dʒiːnz]', 'n.牛仔裤', '1. Every other girl except me is wearing jeans. 除了我以外，其他姑娘都穿著牛仔裤。 2. He wears an oily old pair of jeans. 他穿着一条沾满油污的旧牛仔裤。 3. Both my sister and I like to wear jeans. 我姐姐和我都喜欢穿牛仔裤。 4. The jeans will shrink in the wash. 那些牛仔裤洗过以后会缩水。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immense', '[ɪ\'mens]', 'adj.巨大的；广大的；<口>非常好的', '1. They plunged into their work with immense zeal. 他们以极大的热情投入工作。 2. Her contributions to the state have been immense. 她对国家的贡献极大。 3. It\'s almost impossible to find him in the immense ocean. 在无边无际的海洋中要找到他几乎是不可能的。 4. It were the new comers who had cultivated the immense wilderness. 初来此地的人开辟了这片广袤的荒野。', '副词: immensely 名词: immenseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cluster', '[\'klʌstər]', 'n.群；簇；丛；串 v.群集；丛生；使成群', '1. A cluster of tourists are waiting for their tour guide. 一群游客正在等他们的导游。 2. You can see stars in clusters in the night sky. 你可以看到夜空中的星群。 3. You can see clusters of berries in the garden. 花园里能见到一簇簇浆果。 4. You can see ivy growing in thick clusters anywhere. 到哪儿都能看见成丛生长的常春藤。 5. The men clustered together round the fire and sang songs. 人们聚集在篝火周围唱歌。', '过去式: clustered 过去分词: clustered 现在分词: clustering 第三人称单数: clusters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('whit', '[wɪt]', 'n.些微；一点点', '1. He cares not a whit for public opinion. 他对舆论毫不关心。 2. There\'s not a whit of truth in the statement. 这声明里没有丝毫的真实性。 3. The hostess is every whit as elegant as a lady. 女主人完完全全像贵妇人一样高雅。 4. Linda told her father every whit, and hid nothing from him. 琳达全都告诉了父亲，对他没有一点隐瞒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rainfall', '[\'reɪnfɔːl]', 'n.降雨；降雨量', '1. A rainfall will settle the dust on the road. 一场雨使马路上的尘埃落定。 2. There was another rainfall early this morning. 今天清晨又下了一场雨。 3. This area has very low rainfall. 这个地区雨量稀少。 4. The rainfall averages 36 inches a year. 年降雨量平均为36英寸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crawl', '[krɔːl]', 'v.爬行；卑躬屈膝；自由式游泳 n.爬行；匍匐而行；[体]自由式游泳', '1. The baby is just learning to crawl. 那个婴儿正在学习爬行。 2. Soldiers quietly crawl to advance to enemy. 士兵们悄悄地向敌人匍匐前进。 3. You must not crawl into the favor of your superiors. 你不应卑躬屈膝地讨好你的上司。 4. I hate people who creep and crawl to others. 我讨厌那些阿谀奉承的人。 5. The crawl of snake is terrifying. 蛇爬行起来真可怕。', '副词: crawlingly 过去式: crawled 过去分词: crawled 现在分词: crawling 第三人称单数: crawls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('twine', '[twaɪn]', 'n.合股线；细绳；捻；搓；结 v.缠绕；怀抱；捻；搓；编；蜿蜒', '1. He tied the parcel with twine. 他用细绳来捆扎包裹。 2. The vine twines round the tree. 这藤盘绕在树干上。 3. The girl twined her arms about her mother\'s neck. 女孩搂住母亲的脖子。 4. She twined the flowers into a garland. 她把这些花编成花环。', '名词: twiner 过去式: twined 过去分词: twined 现在分词: twining 第三人称单数: twines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('moron', '[\'mɔːrɑːn]', 'n.笨人', '1. He\'s an absolute moron! 他纯粹是个傻子！ 2. They\'re a load of morons. 他们是一群笨蛋。', '形容词: moronic 副词: moronically 名词: moronism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heal', '[hiːl]', 'vt.治愈；使恢复健康；使和解 vi.痊愈', '1. Time heals most pains. 时间会消除很多痛苦。 2. The medicine and rest will soon heal your wound. 药物治疗和休息会使你的伤口很快愈合。 3. The holy man healed them of their sickness. 那位神职人员治好了他们的疾病。 4. Nothing could heal the rupture between he and his father. 没有什么可以弥合他和父亲之间的裂痕。 5. The terrible wound took a long time to heal. 这重伤费了很长时间才痊愈。', '形容词: healable 过去式: healed 过去分词: healed 现在分词: healing 第三人称单数: heals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frugal', '[\'fruːɡl]', 'adj.节俭的；省钱的', '1. As far as oil energy is concerned, we cannot be too frugal. 就石油能源而言，我们愈节省愈好。 2. They lived a very frugal existence, avoiding all luxuries. 他们生活非常俭朴，力避奢侈。 3. The frugal boy rarely spends money. 那节俭的孩子很少花钱。 4. My mother was also a frugal woman. 我的妈妈也是一位节俭的女人。', '副词: frugally 名词: frugality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shelter', '[\'ʃeltər]', 'n.避难所；庇护；庇护所 v.保护；隐匿；庇护', '1. The refugees\' main requirements are food and shelter. 难民的主要必需品是食物和住所。 2. In the storm I took shelter under the tree. 暴风雨时，我正在树下躲避。 3. The spectators scuttled for shelter when it began to rain. 一下起雨来，观众就纷纷找地方躲避。 4. People were scrambling madly for shelter. 人们疯了似的抢着往隐蔽处跑。 5. These plants must be sheltered from direct sunlight. 这种植物必须遮起来，免受阳光直射。', '形容词: shelterless 名词: shelterer 过去式: sheltered 过去分词: sheltered 现在分词: sheltering 第三人称单数: shelters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crisp', '[krɪsp]', 'adj.脆的；干脆的；卷曲的；明快的；(天气)干冷的 n.薯片；松脆物 v.(使)发脆；(使)卷曲', '1. It tastes sweet and crisp. 吃起来又甜又脆。 2. I like the delicious salad of crisp lettuce and tomatos. 我喜欢这种脆莴苣和番茄做的沙拉，很好吃。 3. Her voice was crisp and authoritative. 她的声音干脆利落，具有权威性。 4. You see how the finish is much more crisp than the rest of the hair. 大家看到了,成型的头发比其余的头发看起来更卷曲。 5. I lay in the sun all day and got burnt to a crisp. 我在太阳下躺了一整天，都快烤焦了。 6. These biscuits have gone soft,you\'d better crisp them up in the oven. 这些饼干变软了，你最好把它们放在烘炉上烤脆。', '副词: crisply 比较级: crisper 最高级: crispest 名词: crispness 过去式: crisped 过去分词: crisped 现在分词: crisping 第三人称单数: crisps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compact', '[\'kɑːmpækt]', 'adj.紧密的；紧凑的；简洁的 vt.使简洁；使装满；压实 n.合约条约；梳妆粉盒；<美>小型汽车', '1. He received a compact package. 他收到一个扎得很紧的包裹。 2. As writers, they like a structure that is compact. 写文章的时候，他们喜欢采用紧凑的结构。 3. Regulator shall be corrosion resistant, compact and lightweight. 这种调节阀应该是耐腐蚀的，紧凑的和轻型的。 4. We\'d love to buy a compact car. 我们想买一辆简洁的车。 5. The kids are try to compact the sand into the mold. 孩子们正在设法把这沙土堆积到模子里。 6. You should sign your name on the right side of the compact. 你应该在合约的右边签上你的名字。', '副词: compactly 名词: compactness 过去式: compacted 过去分词: compacted 现在分词: compacting 第三人称单数: compacts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blunder', '[\'blʌndər]', 'n.大错 v.失策；绊倒；弄糟', '1. He made a blunder in front of his girlfriend. 他在女朋友面前犯了大错。 2. I saw that I had been guilty of a careless blunder. 我意识到自己因疏忽而酿成大错。 3. I made a terrible blunder in introducing her to my husband. 我把她介绍给我的丈夫是犯了一个极大的错误。 4. I hope you will not blunder again . 我希望你不要再犯大错。', '副词: blunderingly 名词: blunderer 过去式: blundered 过去分词: blundered 现在分词: blundering 第三人称单数: blunders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cleft', '[kleft]', 'adj.裂开的；分离的 n.裂缝；开裂 动词cleave的过去式和过去分词.', '1. It provides free operations to children from underprivileged backgrounds with cleft pallets. 这家医院为贫困家庭的唇腭裂患儿提供免费手术。 2. The climber fell down a cleft in the rocks. 爬山者跌入岩石的裂缝里。 3. The man cleft a block of wood in two with an axe. 那人用斧头把一块木头劈成两半。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comparison', '[kəm\'pærɪsn]', 'n.比较；比喻', '1. In comparison with other students, Mike is more diligent. 和其他学生相比，麦克更加勤勉一些。 2. We can only tell good from bad by comparison. 我们可以通过比较来分辨好坏。 3. Reports of consecutive years should also be available for comparison. 网站应登载连续数年的报告,方便读者作比较。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irrigate', '[\'ɪrɪɡeɪt]', 'vi.进行灌溉 vt.灌溉；[医]冲洗', '1. They are irrigating with water. 他们正用水灌溉土地。 2. We have irrigated the desert area to make it fertile. 我们已经灌溉了荒芜地区使它肥沃。 3. They have built canals to irrigate the desert. 他们建造成水渠以灌溉沙漠。 4. They irrigate their crops with water from this river. 他们引这条河里的水灌溉庄稼。', '形容词: irrigational 名词: irrigation 过去式: irrigated 过去分词: irrigated 现在分词: irrigating 第三人称单数: irrigates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decompose', '[ˌdiːkəm\'poʊz]', 'v.分解，拆分，拆解；腐烂', '1. A prism decomposes light. 棱镜可以分解光线。 2. These then decompose to give malonaldehyde. 然后分解生成丙醛酸 3. You can apply heat to decompose organic compounds. 你可以加热来分解有机化合物。 4. There is a decomposing corpse of a deer. 那儿有一具鹿的腐尸。', '形容词: decomposable 名词: decomposability 过去式: decomposed 过去分词: decomposed 现在分词: decomposing 第三人称单数: decomposes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alone', '[ə\'loʊn]', 'adj.单独的；独自一人的；孤单的 adv.独自地；仅仅', '1. Tom is not alone in finding Rick hard to work with. 并不只是汤姆一人认为和里克难以共事。 2. I was alone in the classroom. 我独自在教室里。 3. To tell you the truth, I don\'t feel like being alone tonight. 说实话,我今晚不想孤单一人。 4. After tea I wandered alone about the town. 吃过下午茶,我独自在城里漫步。', '名词: aloneness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('atmosphere', '[\'ætməsfɪr]', 'n.大气；空气；气氛；气压', '1. The burning of fossil fuels results in the pollution of the atmosphere. 矿物燃料的燃烧导致了大气污染。 2. The atmosphere of the city is very much polluted. 那个城市的空气受到严重污染。 3. The atmosphere is very stuffy here and can we open a window? 这里的空气很闷,咱们能打开一扇窗吗？ 4. The atmosphere changed as soon as she walked in. 她一进来气氛就变了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('actual', '[\'æktʃuəl]', 'adj.实际的；事实上的', '1. The actual cause of the quake itself is the rupturing or breaking of rocks at or below the earth\'s surface. 地震本身的真正原因是地球表面的或地底下的岩石断裂或破裂。 2. We call the baby Doc. His actual name is Daniel. 我们把这个婴儿叫做多克,他的实际名字是丹尼尔。 3. I need the actual figures, not an estimate. 我需要确实的数字，不要估计的。 4. My calculation is based on notional figures, since the actual figures are not yet available. 因尚无实际数字，我是根据估计的数字计算的。', '副词: actually');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vessel', '[\'vesl]', 'n.容器；器皿；船；舰；脉管，血管', '1. The simplest calorimeter is a metal vessel used with a thermometer. 最简单的量热计是一个带温度计的金属容器。 2. A pot is a vessel for holding food. 锅是盛食物的器皿。 3. They plotted the new position of each vessel. 他们标明每艘船的新位置。 4. There are some fishing vessels in the harbor. 港湾里有许多渔船。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('policy', '[\'pɑːləsi]', 'n.政策；方针 n.保险单', '1. They expressed their dissent from official policy. 他们对官方的政策表示出异议。 2. I will never swerve from my declared policy on this matter. 我决不背离我已经宣布的在这个问题上的政策。 3. This latest incident may be the lever needed to change government policy. 最近的事件或许可以作为迫使政府改变政策所需的手段。 4. This is a constant policy to conduct our steps. 这是指导我们行动的一贯方针。 5. The annual premium on my policy is 3000 yuan. 我的保险单每年的保险费是三千元。', '名词复数: policies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adapt', '[ə\'dæpt]', 'vt.改编；使适应 vi.适应；适合', '1. This novel has been adapted for radio from the Russian original. 这部小说已由俄文原著改编成无线电广播节目。 2. She adapted herself quickly to the new climate. 她很快就适应了这种新气候。 3. You must adapt to the norms of the society you live in. 在社会中生活就要遵循社会行为准则。 4. It\'s hard to adapt this novel for children. 要将这部小说改编为适合小孩的阅读水准很难。', '过去式: adapted 过去分词: adapted 现在分词: adapting 第三人称单数: adapts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('palate', '[\'pælət]', 'n.上颚；味觉；口味', '1. There is something wrong with my palate. 我的上颚有些不适。 2. I have a good palate for fine wine. 我善于品尝好酒。 3. The fat meat soon disgusted the palate. 大肥肉很快让人吃腻。 4. Spicy food suits my palate best. 辛辣的食物最合我的口味了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jolt', '[dʒoʊlt]', 'n.震摇；摇动；震惊；少量 vt.颠簸；敲击；动摇；震动 vi.颠簸而行', '1. The car stopped with a jolt. 汽车停止时震动了一下。 2. The sudden jolt plunged her forward. 突然颠了一下，她向前打了个趔趄。 3. With a tremendous jolt the car started. 汽车狠狠摇晃一下才起动了。 4. The news came as a jolt. 消息传来,引起震惊。 5. The horse jolted me terribly when he jumped. 马跳跃时,我被颠得很厉害。 6. The cart jolted along over the country road. 二轮货车在农村道路上颠簸着前进。', '形容词: jolty 副词: joltily 名词: jolter 过去式: jolted 过去分词: jolted 现在分词: jolting 第三人称单数: jolts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spiny', '[\'spaɪni]', 'adj.多刺的；尖刺状的；困难的；麻烦的', '1. This is the Asiatic ornamental shrub with spiny branches and pink or red blossoms. 这就是亚洲的一种观赏灌木，具有多刺的枝和粉红色或红色的花。', '比较级: spinier 最高级: spiniest 名词: spininess');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cannibalism', '[\'kænɪbəlɪzəm]', 'n.吃人肉的习性；同类相食', '1. They were forced to practise cannibalism in order to survive. 他们被迫人吃人以求活下去。 2. Cannibalism is perhaps the ultimate cultural taboo. 同类相食也许是人类文化的最高禁忌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pierce', '[pɪrs]', 'v.刺穿；穿透；洞悉 Pierce. n.皮尔斯（人名）', '1. The needle pierced her finger. 针刺进了她的手指。 2. This new type of bullet can pierce armor. 这种新型子弹头能够穿甲。 3. Her shrieks pierced the air. 她尖锐的叫声直刺云天。 4. The regiment pierced through the enemy\'s lines. 这个团突破了敌军防线。', '形容词: piercing 副词: piercingly 名词: piercer 过去式: pierced 过去分词: pierced 现在分词: piercing 第三人称单数: pierces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coherent', '[koʊ\'hɪrənt]', 'adj.连贯的；有条理的；一致的；粘着的', '1. He welded their stories into a single coherent account. 他把他们的故事连在一起写成一个连贯的报导。 2. The subjects of the curriculum form a coherent whole. 课程中的科目构成了一个连贯的整体。 3. She only became coherent again two hours after the attack. 她发病两小时之后才恢复了清楚地说话的能力。 4. She had felt there was something wrong, but couldn\'t give coherent reasons. 她感到有些不对头，但是讲不清楚理由。', '副词: coherently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revitalize', '[ˌriː\'vaɪtəlaɪz]', 'vt.使复兴；使振兴；使复活；使恢复', '1. I think we have to revitalize our society. 我觉得我们的社会需要新生。 2. The Chinese light industry was revitalized in the 1980\'s. 中国轻工业在20世纪80年代重新振兴起来。 3. The shakeup gave Clinton a chance to revitalize his weary team. 此次内阁改组给克林顿以机会使其疲惫的内阁恢复活力。', '名词: revitalization 过去式: revitalized 过去分词: revitalized 现在分词: revitalizing 第三人称单数: revitalizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affluence', '[\'æfluəns]', 'n.富裕', '1. America is a country of great affluence. 美国是富裕的国家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chide', '[tʃaɪd]', 'vi.斥责；指责 vt.(温和地）责备', '1. We chide the citizen because he makes love a commodity. 我们责备庸俗的市民，那是因为他把爱变成了商品。', '副词: chidingly 名词: chider 过去式: chided/chid 过去分词: chided/chid/chidden 现在分词: chiding 第三人称单数: chides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preference', '[\'prefrəns]', 'n.偏爱；优先；喜爱物；优惠', '1. She has a preference for blue. 她特别喜欢蓝色。 2. It\'s entirely a matter of preference. 这完全是个见仁见智的问题。 3. A polar bear has a preference for cold weather. 北极熊喜欢寒冷的天气。 4. While selecting job applicants, we usually give preference to those with some experience. 在筛选求职者的过程中,我们通常优先考虑有一定经验的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('division', '[dɪ\'vɪʒn]', 'n.划分；除法；部门；分开；师（军队）', '1. The divisions between the various classes of society are not so sharply marked as they used to be. 现在社会上各阶级的划分不象过去那样明显了。 2. The boy has learnt to do division. 这个小男孩已学会做除法。 3. He works in the foreign division of the company. 他在公司的外事部工作。 4. There was a division of opinion on the matter. 对于那件事意见分歧。', '形容词: divisional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bloom', '[bluːm]', 'n.花；开花；最佳时期；花期 v.开花；繁盛', '1. The apple-trees are out of bloom. 苹果树已经落了花。 2. Most roses will begin to bloom from late May. 大多数玫瑰从五月末开始开花。 3. The roses are in full bloom. 玫瑰花盛开了。 4. The apple trees are in full bloom at the moment. 目前苹果树开满了花。 5. Daffodils and crocuses bloom in the spring. 水仙花和番红花在春天开放。', '形容词: bloomy 过去式: bloomed 过去分词: bloomed 现在分词: blooming 第三人称单数: blooms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reserve', '[rɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'vt.保留；预订；延期 n.候补；预备品；贮存 n.含蓄；克制', '1. We reserve the right to lodge a claim for loss. 我们保留要求赔偿损失的权利。 2. I have reserved a table at the restaurant. 我已在饭店预订了一桌菜。 3. The court will reserve judgement. 法庭将延期判决。 4. He has played very well on the reserve side but this chance in the first team should put him on his mettle. 他在候补队中表现非常出色,但这次作为正式队员参赛将对他的能力进行考验。 5. He spoke with reserve. 他说话谨慎。', '形容词: reservable 名词: reserver 过去式: reserved 过去分词: reserved 现在分词: reserving 第三人称单数: reserves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gnaw', '[nɔː]', 'v.咬；折磨；侵蚀', '1. Rats gnawed off the lid of the box. 老鼠咬开了盒盖。 2. The rat gnawed a hole through the wall. 耗子在墙上啃了一个洞。 3. These desires gnawed away at us constantly. 这些欲望不断地折磨我们。 4. Self-doubt began to gnaw away at her confidence. 对自己的怀疑渐渐吞噬了她的自信心。', '名词: gnawer 过去式: gnawed 过去分词: gnawed 现在分词: gnawing 第三人称单数: gnaws');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sinuous', '[\'sɪnjuəs]', 'adj.弯弯曲曲的；蜿蜒的；乖僻的', '1. Self-formed river channels tend to be sinuous. 自动形成的河槽是趋向于弯曲的。 2. The river wound its sinuous way across the plain. 这条河蜿蜒曲折地流过平原。', '副词: sinuously 名词: sinuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cogent', '[\'koʊdʒənt]', 'adj.有说服力的；令人信服的', '1. The lawyer\'s cogent arguments convinced the jury. 这位律师很有说服力的争辩使陪审团信服。 2. She put forward some cogent reasons for abandoning the plan. 她为放弃这个计划提出了一些具有说服力的理由。', '副词: cogently 名词: cogency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fraudulent', '[\'frɔːdʒələnt]', 'adj.欺诈的；不正的；不诚实的', '1. This geographic split could be a serious problem for Mexico, if any strife develops in the south over the perception that the election was fraudulent. 假如南方对选举存在欺诈的看法的争吵不断升级，这种地域分歧会成为墨西哥的严重问题。', '副词: fraudulently 名词: fraudulence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('picturesque', '[ˌpɪktʃə\'resk]', 'adj.如画的；生动的；奇特的', '1. The place is remarkable for its picturesque scenery. 这个地方以它的如画的景色著称。 2. The castle stands in a picturesque setting surrounded by hills. 这座城堡四周环山，风景如画。 3. The stable yard fraternity is seldom short of the picturesque word. 稳定的庭院兄弟会很少缺生动的词汇。 4. The picturesque comet is already becoming a favored target for northern sky imagers. 这颗生动的彗星已经成为北天天文摄影者的最爱。', '副词: picturesquely 名词: picturesqueness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('restrain', '[rɪ\'streɪn]', 'vt.抑制；阻止；束缚；剥夺', '1. He couldn\'t restrain his curiosity. 他抑制不住自己的好奇心。 2. She tried to restrain her sobs. 她设法抑制住自己的悲泣。 3. Shame may restrain what the law does not prohibit. 羞耻或许能阻止法律所不能禁止之事。 4. We must not restrain children of their liberty. 我们绝对不要限制孩子们的自由。', '形容词: restrainable 副词: restrainedly 名词: restrainer 过去式: restrained 过去分词: restrained 现在分词: restraining 第三人称单数: restrains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bleed', '[bliːd]', 'v.流血；渗色；榨取；放掉（水或气体）；给...抽血', '1. All the young soldiers are ready to bleed for the country. 所有的年轻战士都愿意为祖国洒热血。 2. If you cut your finger it will bleed. 如果你割破手指,那么它会流血的。 3. A page trimmed so as to bleed. 被剪裁的页次经切裁以印成出血版的纸页 4. The tax man is trying to bleed me white. 税务员正想榨尽我的血汗。', '过去式: bled 过去分词: bled 现在分词: bleeding 第三人称单数: bleeds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clothing', '[\'kloʊðɪŋ]', 'n.(总称)衣服；覆盖物', '1. He discarded his winter clothing. 他把冬天穿的衣服都丢弃了。 2. This clothing sells well to the teenage market. 这种衣服在青少年中间很畅销。 3. Children depend on their parents for food and clothing. 小孩依赖他们的父母供给衣食。 4. We have to put on warm clothing in winter. 冬天的时候，我们不得不穿上温暖的衣服。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convene', '[kən\'viːn]', 'vi.集合 vt.集合；召集；召唤', '1. The tribunal will convene tomorrow. 法庭将于明日开庭。 2. The committee will convene at 11.30 next Thursday. 委员会将在下星期四上午 11:30 开会。 3. The Board shall convene an emergency meeting to review and confirm such report. 董事会应召开紧急会议对该报告进行审议并核准。 4. People were convened here for an emergency meeting. 人们被召集到这里举行紧急会议。', '形容词: convenable 名词: convener 过去式: convened 过去分词: convened 现在分词: convening 第三人称单数: convenes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maneuver', '[mə\'nuːvər]', 'vt.巧妙地操纵；使演习；调遣 vi.演习；调遣；用计策 n.演习；策略；调遣', '1. The mouse had a quick wit and was able to maneuver his way out of danger. 老鼠有急智可以灵巧地脱离危险。 2. They have had to maneuver the ship to avoid unforeseen shoals and shallows. 他们必须设法避开无法预见的暗礁和浅滩。 3. The maneuver aims to strengthen special police forces\' emergency response and combat capabilities. 此次演习的目的在于提高特种警力的危机反应能力和战斗能力。 4. An anti-failure maneuver is very important for power system safety and stability in operation. 反事故演习是保证电网安全稳定运行的重要一环。 5. He must have considered the patrol as an effective maneuver. 他思想上一定还以为派兵侦察是条妙计。', '形容词: maneuverable 名词: maneuverability 过去式: maneuvered 过去分词: maneuvered 现在分词: maneuvering 第三人称单数: maneuvers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('final', '[\'faɪnl]', 'adj.最终的；最后的；决定性的；不可改变的 n.决赛；大学毕业考试；期终考试', '1. The proposal was presented as final package deal. 那项建议是作为最终的一揽子交易提出来的。 2. We are all satisfied with the final result. 我们都对最终的结果感到满意。 3. This is our final offer. 这是我方的最后报价。 4. The game is now in its final stages. 这场比赛现在处于最后阶段。 5. The World Cup final is being transmitted live to over fifty countries. 世界杯决赛现在正向五十多个国家现场转播。', '副词: finally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('garner', '[\'ɡɑːrnər]', 'v.贮藏；收集；得到 n.谷仓 Garner. n.加纳(姓氏)', '1. Squirrels garner nuts for the winter. 松鼠为过冬储存松果。 2. The facts are garnered from various sources. 这些资料是从各种渠道搜集到的。 3. Mr.Smith gradually garnered a national reputation as a financial expert. 史密斯先生逐渐赢得全国金融专家的声誉。 4. Mr. al-Jaafari has been unable to garner support outside his own party. 贾法里一直以来不能得到其他的党派支持。', '过去式: garnered 过去分词: garnered 现在分词: garnering 第三人称单数: garners');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inanimate', '[ɪn\'ænɪmət]', 'adj.无生命的', '1. Rocks and stones are inanimate. 岩石是无生命的。 2. Animals are living beings, not inanimate objects. 动物是生灵，不是没有生命的物体。', '副词: inanimately 名词: inanimateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fitful', '[\'fɪtfl]', 'adj.断断续续的；一阵阵的', '1. The whole debate was rather fitful. 整个辩论断断续续地进行。 2. I studied english fitful for four years. 我断断续续学了四年英语了。 3. I worried half the night and have a fitful sleep. 我半个晚上都一直在担心，故而时醒时睡。', '副词: fitfully 名词: fitfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fatal', '[\'feɪtl]', 'adj.致命的；毁灭性的；决定性的', '1. We gave the enemy a fatal blow. 我们给敌人以致命的打击。 2. There is a fatal flaw in the plan. 计划中有一个致命的缺陷。 3. A possibly fatal crisis may be at hand. 毁灭性的危机可能近在咫尺。 4. The fatal day of the election finally arrived. 大选决定命运的一天终于来到了。', '副词: fatally 名词: fatality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ignorance', '[\'ɪɡnərəns]', 'n.无知；愚昧', '1. He tried to veil his contempt at my ignorance. 他试图掩饰对我的无知的蔑视。 2. I guess ignorance must be a sin. 我认为无知是一种罪。 3. I regret my ignorance on the subject. 我对自己对这个课题的无知感到遗憾。 4. Knowledge makes humble; ignorance makes proud. [谚]知识使人谦虚，无知使人骄傲。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aerobic', '[e\'roʊbɪk]', 'adj.需氧的；有氧的；增氧健身法的', '1. The waste water is initially stored in a series of ponds in which the anaerobic and aerobic treatment is sufficient to irrigate crops. 废水最初放置在一种池子里，使其需氧与厌氧的效应能有用地用于灌溉作物。 2. Because GSH is also essential to aerobic muscular contraction, an undesirable competition for GSH precursors between the immune and muscular systems may develop. 由于谷胱甘肽对耗氧的肌肉收缩也至关重要，而造成我们不欲见到的免疫系统和肌肉系统间对谷胱甘肽前体的竞争。 3. The waste water is initially stored in a series of ponds in which the anaerobic and aerobic treatment is sufficient to irrigate crops. 废水最初放置在一种池子里，使其需氧与厌氧的效应能有用地用于灌溉作物。 4. Because GSH is also essential to aerobic muscular contraction, an undesirable competition for GSH precursors between the immune and muscular systems may develop. 由于谷胱甘肽对耗氧的肌肉收缩也至关重要，而造成我们不欲见到的免疫系统和肌肉系统间对谷胱甘肽前体的竞争。', '副词: aerobically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amicable', '[\'æmɪkəbl]', 'adj.友好的；和睦的', '1. We came to an amicable agreement. 我们达成了友好的协议。 2. Especially when you\'ve established a long-term good business relationship with us,it is usually much easier to handle the disputes through amicable negotiations. 尤其当我们双方之间建立了长期友好的贸易关系以后，通过友好协商来解决争议就更容易了。 3. Unwedding ceremony acknowledges their shared life and marks their amicable separation. 离婚仪式承认彼此曾经共同拥有的生活，并且表示出他们彼此和睦的分离。', '副词: amicably 名词: amicability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dispatch', '[dɪ\'spætʃ]', 'v.派遣；发送；迅速完成；处死 n.急件；派遣；发送；新闻报道', '1. A messenger was dispatched to take the news to the soldiers at the front. 一名通讯员被派去给前线士兵送消息。 2. We have to ask you to dispatch the consignment immediately. 我们得要求你立即发送该批货物。 3. We soon dispatched the chocolate cake. 我们很快就吃完了那个巧克力蛋糕。 4. The criminal will be dispatched today. 那名罪犯将于今日被处决。 5. I threw the dispatch to him and asked him to take prompt actions. 我把那份急件扔给他,让他立刻采取措施。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('melody', '[\'melədi]', 'n.旋律；曲子；曲调；美妙的音乐', '1. The melody still rang in her ears. 那个旋律仍然在她的耳际荡。 2. The organist played a famous melody. 这位管风琴手演奏了一首著名的曲子。 3. He played a delightful melody on his flute. 他用笛子吹奏了欢快的曲调。 4. The song has plaintive melody. 这首歌曲的曲调悲伤。', '名词复数: melodies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vivid', '[\'vɪvɪd]', 'adj.生动的；鲜艳的；栩栩如生的', '1. This place conjures up vivid memories. 这个地方使人回忆起许多生动的往事。 2. My daughter is a child with vivid imagination. 我女儿是一个想象力活跃的孩子。 3. This girl gave a vivid description of the event. 那女孩对这件事作了一番生动的描述。 4. Only the vivid red hair ever stood out. 只有鲜艳的红头发非常令人注目。', '副词: vividly 比较级: vivider 最高级: vividest 名词: vividness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('holocaust', '[\'hɑːləkɔːst]', 'n.大屠杀；浩劫；燔祭', '1. Suddenly there is a nuclear holocaust. 突然之间产生了一个核弹大屠杀。 2. He was a descendent of Holocaust survivors. 他是大屠杀幸存者的后代。 3. He predicted that there would be a world holocaust. 他预言将有一场世界性的浩劫。 4. I know this sounds like preparations for a nuclear holocaust, but the effects could be horrifyingly similar. 我知道这听起来一定像是为核浩劫提前准备，但其结果其实都挺恐怖的。', '形容词: holocaustal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recover', '[rɪ\'kʌvər]', 'v.恢复；复原；重获', '1. He\'s now fully recovered from his stroke. 他现已从中风病完全康复了。 2. He is very ill and unlikely to recover. 他病得非常厉害，不大可能恢复健康了。 3. I nearly fell but managed to recover myself. 我差一点倒下,但最后还是站稳了脚根。 4. I sat down to recover from my agitation. 我坐下以使自己平静下来。', '形容词: recoverable 名词: recoverer 过去式: recovered 过去分词: recovered 现在分词: recovering 第三人称单数: recovers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('terminology', '[ˌtɜːrmə\'nɑːlədʒi]', 'n.术语；术语学', '1. Don\'t punish our brain with technical terminology. 别用术语来让我们伤脑筋了。 2. The article uses rather specialized musical terminology. 这篇文章用了相当专业的音乐术语。 3. Terminology is a complex cross-disciplinary science. 术语学是一门综合性的应用学科。 4. All language professionals acknowledge the crucial role of terminology. 语言工作者均了解术语学的重要作用。', '形容词: terminological 副词: terminologically 名词: terminologist 名词复数: terminologies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bombastic', '[bɒm\'bæstɪk]', 'adj.夸大的', '1. The orator spoke in a bombastic manner. 这位演说家的讲话言过其实。 2. The candidate spoke in a bombastic way of all that he would do if elected. 候选人大肆吹嘘,一旦他当选将要如何如何。 3. The chairperson of this commission criticised that the police had adoped bombast gestures. 该委员会的主度批评了警方采取的高调姿态。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evidence', '[\'evɪdəns]', 'n.证据；证词；根据；迹象 v.证明；证实', '1. There wasn\'t enough evidence to prove his guilt. 没有充分的证据能证明他有罪。 2. Evidence weighted against the defendant. 证词很不利于被告。 3. It is a statement in conflict with other evidence. 这一陈述与其他证词不一致。 4. Have you any evidence to support this statement? 你这种说法有根据吗? 5. His answer evidenced a guilty conscience. 他的回答证明他良心有愧。', '过去式: evidenced 过去分词: evidenced 现在分词: evidencing 第三人称单数: evidences');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('palatable', '[\'pælətəbl]', 'adj.美味的；使人愉快的；遂心如意的', '1. Mother provides palatable meals for our family every day. 母亲每天为家人烹制美味的三餐。 2. Chinese dishes are exquisitely prepared,delicious,and very palatable. 中国菜做得十分精细、美味，非常好吃。 3. My advice may not be palatable, but they were sincerely meant. 我的劝告也许不令人愉快，但用意却甚诚恳。 4. The truth is not always very palatable . 事实真相并非尽如人意.', '副词: palatably 名词: palatability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sloppy', '[\'slɑːpi]', 'adj.肥大的；潦草的；草率的；稀薄的；庸俗感伤的', '1. At home I tend to wear big sloppy jumpers and jeans. 在家里我喜欢穿宽大的套衫和牛仔裤。 2. I can\'t decipher his sloppy handwriting. 我无法辨认他那潦草的字迹。 3. She lectured him on his sloppy demeanor. 她谴责他那种草率的态度。 4. I hate sloppy romantic films. 我讨厌那些庸俗伤感的爱情片。', '副词: sloppily 比较级: sloppier 最高级: sloppiest 名词: sloppiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annoyed', '[ə\'nɔɪd]', 'adj.恼怒的；气恼的 动词annoy的过去式和过去分词.', '1. I was so annoyed that I felt impelled to write a letter to the paper. 我非常恼怒，以致觉得非给报社写封信不可。 2. His attitude made me extremely annoyed. 他的态度使我十分气恼。 3. I\'m extremely annoyed at the way he always stares at me in the office. 他在办公室里老是目不转睛地盯着我,真把我气坏了。 4. The wantonness of the girl\'s character annoyed us. 那个女孩变化无常的性格让我们很生气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advice', '[əd\'vaɪs]', 'n.劝告；忠告；建议', '1. Tell me the reason (why) he refused to listen to my advice. 告诉我为何他拒绝听从我的劝告。 2. He disregarded his doctor\'s advice. 他无视医生的劝告。 3. I set a high value on his advice. 我认为他的忠告很有价值。 4. I asked the teacher for her advice. 我征求这位老师的意见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meddle', '[\'medl]', 'v.干涉', '1. Don\'t meddle in my affairs. 别干预我的事情。 2. Do not meddle with the tools. 不要乱动工具。 3. He is inclined to meddle in other people\'s affairs. 他总喜欢干涉别人的事。', '名词: meddler 过去式: meddled 过去分词: meddled 现在分词: meddling 第三人称单数: meddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('label', '[\'leɪbl]', 'n.标记；标签；称号；唱片公司 vt.贴标签于；把 ... 归类', '1. Put a label on your luggage. 在你行李上做个标记。 2. I read the information on the label before deciding which jam to buy. 我先看果酱标签上的说明再决定买哪种. 3. He has been given a label of \"playboy\" by his friends. 他的朋友给他起了一个“花花公子”的绰号。 4. It\'s his first release for a major label. 这是他在大唱片公司发行的第一张唱片。 5. The bottle is labeled poison. 瓶上标明有毒。', '名词: labeler 过去式: labeled/labelled 过去分词: labeled/labelled 现在分词: labeling/labelling 第三人称单数: labels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slogan', '[\'sloʊɡən]', 'n.口号；标语', '1. The advertising slogan was a play on words. 那条广告口号是双关语。 2. A slogan is over the blackboard. 一条标语在黑板正上方。 3. He daubed the wall with a slogan. 他在墙上写了一条标语。 4. A product will sell better if it is promoted with a slogan. 如果用标语促销,产品的销势会更好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('curtail', '[kɜːr\'teɪl]', 'v.缩减；削减；截短', '1. Illness has curtailed her sporting activities. 她因病而减少了体育活动。 2. The government hopes to curtail public spending. 政府希望缩减公共事业开支。 3. The government hopes to curtail public spending in the next tax year. 政府希望在下个财税年度减少公家开支。 4. Given this, China will continue to take measures to curtail the trend of deflation. 因此,中国还要继续采取措施以遏制通缩的趋势。', '名词: curtailer 过去式: curtailed 过去分词: curtailed 现在分词: curtailing 第三人称单数: curtails');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sledding', '[sledɪŋ]', 'n.坐雪橇；进展 动词sled的现在分词形式.', '1. The children took turns sledding down the hill. 孩子们轮流坐雪橇滑下山丘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('magnetic', '[mæɡ\'netɪk]', 'adj.有磁性的；有吸引力的；催眠术的 n.磁体，磁性物质', '1. The loop becomes magnetic when the current is switched on. 通电时线圈就会有磁性。 2. She has a magnetic personality. 她具有极具吸引力的性格。 3. She was the most magnetic speaker I have ever listened to. 她是我所听过的演讲者中最有吸引力的一位。', '副词: magnetically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bereave', '[bɪ\'riːv]', 'vt.剥夺；使丧失', '1. The accident bereaved him of his wife and child. 车祸夺去了他的妻子和儿子的生命。 2. Indignation bereft him of speech. 他气愤得说不出话来。', '名词: bereavement 过去式: bereaved/bereft 过去分词: bereaved/bereft 现在分词: bereaving 第三人称单数: bereaves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('removal', '[rɪ\'muːvl]', 'n.移动；搬迁；除去；开除', '1. The removal of a neutron from the system is indicated by the head of an arrow. 用箭头表示一个中子从这个系统中的移动。 2. We haven\'t told our friends about our removal to London. 我们还没有告诉我们的朋友我们搬家到伦敦了。 3. Our ultimate objective is the removal of all nuclear weapons. 我们的最终目标是消除所有核武器。 4. Their removal is effected by aluminum and ferric salts. 用铁盐和铝盐能将其有效地除去。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commence', '[kə\'mens]', 'v.开始；着手；<英>获得学位', '1. I commence from this point. 我从此点开始。 2. The second term commences in March. 第二学期自三月开始。 3. We will commence with this work. 我们要着手进行这项工作。 4. I commence a round of visit. 我开始着手一系列访问。', '名词: commencer 过去式: commenced 过去分词: commenced 现在分词: commencing 第三人称单数: commences');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('method', '[\'meθəd]', 'n.方法；条理 n.类函数；类成员函数（计算机）', '1. I have a simple and easy method. 我有个简易的方法。 2. New methods of teaching foreign languages are adopted in this institute. 该学院采用新的外语教学法。 3. His book is totally without method. 他写的那本书毫无条理。 4. We must get some method into our office filing. 我们必须把公文归档工作弄出些条理来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prime', '[praɪm]', 'adj.最好的；首要的；典型的 n.壮年；全盛时期；青春 n.[数]质数 vt.事先指点；在（金属、木材等上）打底漆 vi.变得首要', '1. He reached his prime and then, when he had the most to live for, he died. 他到了壮年时期,该做出最大贡献,活得最好的时候,却死掉了。 2. We were well prime for the journey with a large breakfast. 为了去旅行,我们早餐都吃得饱饱的。 3. What was said was of prime importance. 说过的那件事是很重要的。 4. Britain has a queen, but it is the prime minister and the cabinet who govern. 英国有女王,但执政的是首相和内阁。 5. He died in the prime of his life. 他在壮年时死去。 6. It states that every even number greater than two can be expressed as the sum of two primes (a prime is a number that is only divisible by itself and by 1, such as 7 and 13). 其陈述是：每一个大于2的偶数都可以表达成两个素数之和(素数是指只能被1和它本身整除的数，如7和13)。 7. She has been well primed about what to say. 她已经有人指点,知道要说些什么。 8. Peace is the prime objective of our foreign policy. 我们把争取和平作为对外政策的首要任务。', '副词: primely 名词: primeness 过去式: primed 过去分词: primed 现在分词: priming 第三人称单数: primes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inconceivable', '[ˌɪnkən\'siːvəbl]', 'adj.不可思议的；难以置信的', '1. That event was inconceivable to us. 那件事是我们所想像不到的。 2. It is inconceivable that a thing can both be and not be. 一件事情，即是又非是，是不可思议的。 3. It once seemed inconceivable to everyone that men should travel to the moon. 人们一度认为，人飞上月球似乎是不可想象的。 4. It is inconceivable that the minister was not aware of the problem. 令人难以置信的是那位大臣竟然没有意识到这个问题。', '副词: inconceivably 名词: inconceivability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overflow', '[ˌoʊvər\'floʊ]', 'v.泛滥；溢出；充满；洋溢 n.泛滥；溢值；剩出', '1. We must harness the rivers which overflow annually. 我们必须治理那些每年泛滥的河流。 2. The river overflowed its banks. 河水漫过了两岸。 3. The crowd overflowed the auditorium. 人群挤得礼堂无法容纳。 4. Her heart was overflowing with joy. 她的心里洋溢着喜悦。 5. Put a bowl underneath to catch the overflow. 把盆放在下面接住溢出物。', '过去式: overflowed 过去分词: overflowed 现在分词: overflowing 第三人称单数: overflows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sponsor', '[\'spɑːnsər]', 'n.保证人；赞助者；发起者；主办者 v.发起；赞助；倡议', '1. Your sponsor may assist in organising this insurance. 你的担保人可以帮助你办理此类保险。 2. Mr. Robert Brown was announced as the sponsor. 罗勃特·布朗先生被宣布为赞助人。 3. A wealthy sponsor came to our rescue with a generous donation. 有个富有的赞助人慷慨捐赠来解救我们。 4. Who is the sponsor of the research program? 谁是这个研究项目的发起人? 5. The senator announced that he would sponsor the health care plan. 这位参议员宣布他将发起这一保健计划。', '形容词: sponsorial 名词: sponsorship 过去式: sponsored 过去分词: sponsored 现在分词: sponsoring 第三人称单数: sponsors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('construe', '[kən\'struː]', 'v.解释；翻译；作句法分析', '1. His remarks were wrongly construed. 他的话被错误地解释了。 2. You can construe what he said in a number of different ways. 他的话可以有好几种解释。 3. How do you construe what he did? 你对他之所为作何解释? 4. This sentence is difficult to construe. 这个句子很难翻译。', '过去式: construed 过去分词: construed 现在分词: construing 第三人称单数: construes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('communicate', '[kə\'mjuːnɪkeɪt]', 'v.传达；沟通；交流', '1. He has communicated his wishes to me. 他已经把他的愿望告诉了我。 2. I like to communicate with my family. 我喜欢和我的家人沟通。 3. The door communicates with my room. 这门和我的房间相通。 4. Good manners are not only about the way we talk, but also about all other things we do when we communicate with other people. 好的礼节不仅仅是指我们谈话的方式,还包括我们在与别人交流时进行各种活动的处理办法与态度。', '名词: communicator 过去式: communicated 过去分词: communicated 现在分词: communicating 第三人称单数: communicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heave', '[hiːv]', 'v.用力举起；抛出；扔；恶心；（费力地）发出（叹息等） n.举；抛；起伏', '1. They heave at the heavy box, but can not lift it. 他们想搬动那只很重的箱子，但抬不起来。 2. He hove a chair through the window. 他把椅子从窗户中抛出。 3. Heave the rocks into the ravine. 把这些石头扔进深谷里。 4. It\'s a very bad thing to heave things around. 把东西到处乱扔是很不好的习惯。 5. With one more heave, we got the box onto the shelf. 我们再使把劲,就把箱子抬到架子上了。', '名词: heaver 过去式: heaved 过去分词: heaved 现在分词: heaving 第三人称单数: heaves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('marble', '[\'mɑːrbl]', 'n.大理石；弹子，弹珠 vt.使有大理石的花纹', '1. This table is made of marble. 这个桌子是大理石的。 2. Michelangelo carved in marble. 米开朗琪罗在大理石上雕刻。 3. There are many perpendicular marble columns in Greek temples. 希腊庙宇有很多垂直的大理石柱。 4. My little son has many marbles. 我的小儿子有许多弹珠。', '形容词: marbly 过去式: marbled 过去分词: marbled 现在分词: marbling 第三人称单数: marbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('industrial', '[ɪn\'dʌstriəl]', 'adj.工业的；产业的 n.工业公司', '1. She is an industrial designer. 她是工业设计师。 2. The industrial exposition will be held on September. 工业博览会将于九月召开。 3. The industrial revolution had taken place in England first. 工业革命首先在英国发生。 4. Due to low investment, our industrial output has remained stagnant. 由于投资少，我们的工业生产一直停滞不前。 5. He troubleshoots for a large industrial firm. 他受雇为一家大工业公司检修故障。', '副词: industrially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cactus', '[\'kæktəs]', 'n.仙人掌', '1. We have to water this cactus once a month. 我们必须每月给仙人掌浇一次水。 2. The candy made from cactus tastes strange. 用仙人掌做的糖果味道很怪。', '名词复数: cacti');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mathematics', '[ˌmæθə\'mætɪks]', 'n.数学', '1. Mathematics is her favorite subject. 数学是她喜欢的科目。 2. He has a great faculty for mathematics. 他具有很强的学数学的才能。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('punctual', '[\'pʌŋktʃuəl]', 'adj.准时的；严守时刻的；正点的', '1. My cat makes a punctual appearance at mealtimes. 我的猫一到用餐时间就会准时出现。 2. Please be punctual in futurity. 今后请准时。 3. He likes his guests to be punctual. 他喜欢客人守时。 4. Not being punctual is his greatest shortcoming. 不守时间是他的最大缺点。', '副词: punctually 名词: punctuality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inevitable', '[ɪn\'evɪtəbl]', 'adj.不可避免的；必然(发生)的', '1. You\'ll have to bow to the inevitable. 你将不得不向不可避免的事态低头。 2. But most agree that change is inevitable. 但她们多数人同意改变是不可避免的。', '副词: inevitably 名词: inevitability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('witty', '[\'wɪti]', 'adj.机智的；诙谐的', '1. His witty remark caused a storm of laughter. 他的妙语引起一阵哄堂大笑。 2. You are an honorable and witty doctor. 你是个正直而机智的博士。 3. She responded to their criticism with a witty retort. 她以机智的反驳回应了他们的批评。 4. He relieved the silence with witty jokes. 他以诙谐的笑话解除沉默。', '副词: wittily 比较级: wittier 最高级: wittiest 名词: wittiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contemplate', '[\'kɑːntəmpleɪt]', 'vt.注视；沉思；打算', '1. He stood contemplating the painting. 他站着审视那幅图画。 2. It terrified me to contemplate the consequence of your action. 一想到你行动的后果,我就感到害怕。 3. The doctor contemplated the difficult operation he had to perform. 医生细想他要进行的棘手的手术。 4. We contemplate obtaining a technical license. 我们希望获得一项技术许可证。', '名词: contemplator 过去式: contemplated 过去分词: contemplated 现在分词: contemplating 第三人称单数: contemplates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chaos', '[\'keɪɑːs]', 'n.混乱；无秩序；混沌', '1. The wintry weather has caused chaos on the roads. 因风雪交加,道路上混乱不堪。 2. After the failure of the electricity supplies, the city was in chaos. 电力供应中断,城市陷于混乱之中。 3. Without rules, people would live in a state of chaos. 若无规则,人们将在混乱状态中生活。 4. Chaos often breeds life, when order breeds habit. 混沌常常孕育着生命，而秩序会产生习惯。', '形容词: chaotic 副词: chaotically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legislature', '[\'ledʒɪsleɪtʃər]', 'n.立法机关', '1. He was an outstanding member of the legislature. 他是立法机关的杰出成员。 2. Do you know what is the legislature in China? 你知道中国的立法机关是哪个吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('candidate', '[\'kændɪdət]', 'n.候选人；应试者', '1. There are three candidates for the vacancy. 这一空缺有三名候选人。 2. She had been nominated as candidate for the presidency. 她已被提名为总统候选人。 3. He made several favorable comments about their candidate. 他对他们的候选人发表了一些有利的评论。 4. Most candidates passed in grammar. 参加考试的人大多数语法及格。', '名词: candidacy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aboriginal', '[ˌæbə\'rɪdʒənl]', 'adj.原始的；土著的 n.土著居民；土生生物', '1. And it is only the white locals who profit from the tourist industry by peddling Aboriginal cultural artifacts such as didgeridoos and boomerangs. 白当地居民从土著的文化产物的旅游工业来获取利益，比如迪吉里杜管和回飞棒。', '副词: aboriginally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immunity', '[ɪ\'mjuːnəti]', 'n.免疫；免疫性；免除；豁免', '1. Children who have gotten the chickenpox build an immunity to it so that they do not get it a second time. 已经得过水痘的小孩会对它免疫,所以不会再得第二次。 2. This vaccine will give you immunity for two years. 接种这种疫苗可有两年免疫力。 3. Nobody will be given immunity from taxation. 没有人可以免除被征税。 4. He has diplomatic immunity. 他有外交豁免权。', '名词复数: immunities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cuneiform', '[\'kjuːnɪfɔːrm]', 'adj.楔形的；楔形文字的 n.楔形文字；楔形骨', '1. The cuneiform script is a great invention by the Sumerians. 楔形文字是苏美尔人的一大发明。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('territory', '[\'terətɔːri]', 'n.领土；领域；版图；范围', '1. The territory was carved up by the occupying powers. 领土被侵占者瓜分。 2. Each of the two countries claimed the territory. 这两个国家各自声称这片领土是自己的。 3. He seems to regard that end of the office as his territory. 他把办公室的那一头看成是他的地盘。 4. Our country is vast in territory. 我国版图辽阔。', '名词复数: territories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('futile', '[\'fjuːtl]', 'adj.无效的；无用的', '1. Pace considers attempts at timing futile. 贝斯认为企图控制时间是无效的。 2. We are the Borg, Earth assimilation is inevitable, Resistant is futile! 我们是博格，地球将被同化，抵抗是无效的！ 3. It is futile to attempt to convince him that certain things are simply undoable. 使他相信某事情是完全不可为的是无用的尝试。 4. Any unrealistic objective is not worth pursuing sedulously since it is doomed to a futile project. 任何不现实的目标不值得去辛苦地追求因为它注定是无用的计划。', '副词: futilely 名词: futileness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irreconcilable', '[ɪ\'rekənsaɪləbl]', 'adj.不能和解的；不能协调的；矛盾的', '1. The separated couple was irreconcilable. 那对分居的夫妻不可能和解。 2. This is an irreconcilable conflict. 这是一个不可调和的矛盾。 3. We can never agree our views are irreconcilable. 我们永远不能一致--彼此的看法无法调和。 4. Good and evil are irreconcilable. 善与恶不可调和。', '副词: irreconcilably 名词: irreconcilability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('medium', '[\'miːdiəm]', 'adj.中等的；适中的 n.手段；媒介；媒体', '1. The blue cap is a medium size. 那顶蓝色的帽子就是中号的。 2. The clothes should be washed at medium temperature. 这衣服需以适中温度洗涤。 3. Commercial television is an effective medium for advertising. 商业电视是有效的广告宣传工具。 4. Sound travels through the medium of air. 声音通过空气这一媒介传播。', '名词复数: media');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devoid', '[dɪ\'vɔɪd]', 'adj.全无的；缺乏的', '1. In the universe which appears to be uderly devoid of humor.We enjoy the superior luxury. 在一个幽默全无的宇宙里，我们享有这一至高无上的财富。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('depict', '[dɪ\'pɪkt]', 'vt.描述；描绘；画', '1. Her novel depicts life in modern London. 她的小说描写的是伦敦现代的生活。 2. The book depicts him as a rather unpleasant character. 这本书把他刻画成一个相当令人讨厌的人物。 3. This painting depicts the birth of Venus. 这幅画描绘的是维纳斯的诞生。 4. It\'s a picture depicting him as a clown. 这是一幅把他画成小丑的画。', '名词: depiction 过去式: depicted 过去分词: depicted 现在分词: depicting 第三人称单数: depicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mention', '[\'menʃn]', 'vt.提到；说起 n.提及；说起', '1. Speaking of Macao, it is necessary to mention lotus flowers. 说到澳门,就不得不提到莲花了。 2. Paul is highly intelligent, not to mention good-looking and rich. 保罗学识渊博,更不用说他还英俊富有呢! 3. He made no mention of having met her. 他不提他曾经和她见面。 4. She blushed at the mention of her love\'s name . 她因说到她情人的名字而脸红。', '形容词: mentionable 过去式: mentioned 过去分词: mentioned 现在分词: mentioning 第三人称单数: mentions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chief', '[tʃiːf]', 'adj.主要的；首要的 n.首领', '1. In USA, NewYork City is the chief seat of commerce. 在美国,纽约是主要的商业中心。 2. What are the chief exports of your country? 你们国家有哪些主要的出口物品？ 3. Slow speed is the chief drawback of sea shipment. 海运最大的缺点是速度慢。 4. The chief interchanged the diamond with some pieces of glass. 那首领拿一些玻璃块替换了那些钻石。', '名词: chiefdom');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ballot', '[\'bælət]', 'n.投票；投票用纸 vi.投票', '1. We should put it to a ballot. 我们应该对此进行无记名投票。 2. He was elected by ballot. 他是由无记名投票选举的。 3. The new act stipulates that election to union office shall be by secret ballot of members. 新法规定工会职位的选举将由会员秘密投票方式进行。 4. Each voter receives a unique ballot code. 每一个投票人会收到一个独一的选票号码。 5. They decided to ballot for competing lanes. 他们决定抽签选择比赛跑道。', '名词: balloter 过去式: balloted 过去分词: balloted 现在分词: balloting 第三人称单数: ballots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devise', '[dɪ\'vaɪz]', 'vt.设计；发明；遗赠', '1. This time we\'ll devise a better solution. 这次我们将设计一种新的解决方案。 2. The government devised a scheme for redeveloping the city center. 政府制定了市中心重建计划。 3. He devised a new type of transistor. 他发明了一种新的晶体管。', '形容词: devisable 名词: deviser 过去式: devised 过去分词: devised 现在分词: devising 第三人称单数: devises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('qualified', '[\'kwɑːlɪfaɪd]', 'adj.有资格的；有保留的；有限制的；能胜任的', '1. He\'s not qualified for this job. 他不能胜任这项工作。 2. We need more qualified science worker. 我们需要更多合格的科学工作者。 3. He is well qualified for the work. 他有充分的资格担任该工作。 4. Strictly speaking, he\'s not qualified for the job. 严格说来，他没有资格做这份工作。', '副词: qualifiedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dispensable', '[dɪ\'spensəbl]', 'adj.不是必要的；可有可无的', '1. A garage is useful but dispensable. 汽车房虽然有用 2. He repents having compensated the dispensable pesion for fear of penalty. 他后悔因害怕处罚而补偿了不必要的养老金。 3. They looked on music and art lessons as dispensable. 他们认为音乐课和美术课是可有可无的。 4. Otherwise Miller would become a dispensable figurehead. 否则米勒就会变成可有可无的傀儡。', '名词: dispensability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deform', '[dɪ\'fɔːrm]', 'vt.使变形；使畸形 vi.变形', '1. Sitting badly for long periods of time can deform your spine. 长时间的错误坐姿会使你的脊柱变形。 2. Shoes that are too tight deform the feet. 太紧的鞋使脚变形。 3. His leg was deformed in an accident. 他的腿在一次事故中致畸。 4. She has a deformed foot and can\'t walk very easily. 她有一只脚畸形，行动不方便。 5. The silver was deformed under stress. 银在压力作用下变了形。', '形容词: deformable 名词: deformability 过去式: deformed 过去分词: deformed 现在分词: deforming 第三人称单数: deforms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ignominious', '[ˌɪɡnə\'mɪniəs]', 'adj.可耻的；不名誉的', '1. The waste is one kind of ignominious behavior. 浪费是一种可耻的行为。 2. The conspiracy frittered away to an ignominious conclusion. 那个阴谋以可耻的失败而告终。 3. He made one mistake and his career came to an ignominious end. 他犯了一个错误，他的事业就很不体面地结束了。 4. There is a long, ignominious tradition in this nation of violence toward newcomers. 这个国家有个不光彩的传统，那就是对于初来乍到者的不友好。', '副词: ignominiously 名词: ignominiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advise', '[əd\'vaɪz]', 'vt.劝告；通知；忠告；建议 vi.提建议', '1. They advised her against marrying quickly. 他们劝她不要太快结婚。 2. Please advise us when the goods are dispatched. 请通知我们何时发货。 3. He can advise on how to learn English well. 他能就如何学好英语提出忠告。 4. I would advise you to keep out of the way when the teacher is rousting out the bad boys in the class. 我要忠告你，当老师训斥班上调皮学生的时候，你要避开一点。 5. The effective work of maintaining discipline is usually performed by students who advise the academic authorities. 而有效遵守纪律的学生们往往是那些经常给校方提建议的学生。', '过去式: advised 过去分词: advised 现在分词: advising 第三人称单数: advises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cling', '[klɪŋ]', 'vi.紧贴；附着；依恋；坚持 n.紧抓；紧贴', '1. The wet clothes clung to his body. 湿衣服紧贴在他身上。 2. He clung to my arm. 他紧抓着我的胳膊。 3. The cat tried to cling to the edge by its claws. 猫用爪子拼命抓住那边缘。 4. Little children always cling to their mothers. 小孩子总是紧依着母亲。 5. The droid used his magnetized rollers to cling tenaciously to the chromed surface of the ship while deadly turbolaser blasts rained overhead. 在致命的雷射光炮不停地打落在太空船上时，他用具有磁性的滚轮紧抓住舰艇铬制的表面。', '形容词: clingy 名词: clinger 过去式: clung 过去分词: clung 现在分词: clinging 第三人称单数: clings');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pretentious', '[prɪ\'tenʃəs]', 'adj.自命不凡的；自负的；矫饰的；炫耀的', '1. He is a talented but pretentious writer. 他是一个有才华但自命不凡的作家。 2. That young man is extremely pretentious. 那个年轻人非常自命不凡。 3. He imposed his pretentious books on the public. 他把他写的自认为不错的书强行推销给大众。 4. People are so much more pretentious nowadays. 现在的人比以前浮华得多。', '副词: pretentiously 名词: pretentiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('therapy', '[\'θerəpi]', 'n.疗法；治疗', '1. The scraping therapy is very popular in China. 在中国刮痧疗法很受欢迎。 2. Physical therapy alternates with chemical. 理疗和化疗交替进行。 3. She was in therapy. 她正在接受治疗。 4. Self-help is an important element in therapy for the handicapped. 伤残人士在治疗中，自助自立是个重要因素。', '名词复数: therapies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expand', '[ɪk\'spænd]', 'v.使 ... 膨胀；详述；扩张；增加；张开', '1. Metals expand when they are heated. 金属遇热则膨胀。 2. Would you expand upon the matter a little further? 请你再进一步谈谈这件事好吗? 3. They conferred on the best way to expand business. 他们商议扩展业务的最好方法。 4. Our foreign trade has expanded during recent years. 近年来我们的对外贸易有所增加。', '形容词: expandable 名词: expander 过去式: expanded 过去分词: expanded 现在分词: expanding 第三人称单数: expands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conclusive', '[kən\'kluːsɪv]', 'adj.决定性的；确实的；结论性的', '1. It was not a war that promised a conclusive end. 那并不是一场指望有决定性结果的战争。 2. They produced some fairly conclusive evidence. 他们提供了一些相当确凿的证据。 3. Her fingerprints on the gun were conclusive proof of her guilt. 她在枪上留下的指纹就是她犯罪的确凿证据。 4. These arguments, particularly the last one, were conclusive. 这些理由,特别是最后一个,是毫无争论余地的。', '副词: conclusively 名词: conclusiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('age', '[eɪdʒ]', 'n.年龄；时代；时期；长时间 v.（使）变老；（使）陈化', '1. What is your age? 你多大年纪？ 2. The child is at an impressionable age. 这孩子正处于易受影响的年龄。 3. We are living in the age of technology. 我们生活在工业技术时代。 4. Rome was in its prime in the age of Augustus. 罗马帝国的全盛期是在奥古斯都时代。 5. Anxiety ages us. 忧虑催人老。', '名词: ager 过去式: aged 过去分词: aged 现在分词: aging 第三人称单数: ages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exterior', '[ɪk\'stɪriər]', 'n.外部；外表；外景 adj.外部的；表面的；对外的；户外的', '1. Advertising normally produces a design for the exterior of the container. 广告部一般是作包装的外部设计。 2. The exterior of the building is very unattractive. 这建筑物的外观很不起眼。 3. He is a gentle man with a rough exterior. 他是一个外表粗鲁但性情温和的男人。 4. She maintained a calm exterior, though really she was furious. 在外表上她保持着平静，但实际上她生气极了。 5. We are painting the exterior wall of the house. 我们正在给房子的外墙涂漆。', '副词: exteriorly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('versatile', '[\'vɜːrsətl]', 'adj.多才多艺的；通用的；多功能的', '1. Versatile actors can play all kinds of roles. 多才多艺的演员能演各种类型的角色。 2. He is one of the most versatile actors. 他是最多才多艺的演员之一。 3. These cotton towels are quite versatile for this reason. 鉴于这点,这些毛巾都是通用的。 4. I bought a versatile kitchen machine last month. 我上个月买了一部多功能的厨房用机器.', '副词: versatilely 名词: versatility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reinforce', '[ˌriːɪn\'fɔːrs]', 'vt.加固；加强；增强；使更具说服力 vi.得到加强', '1. We will use metal strap to reinforce the outside. 我们会在纸箱外用金属带加固。 2. Any good speaker should be able to reinforce his argument with facts. 一个好的演讲者会用事实来加强他论点。 3. Public reaction will reinforce it. 社会反响会进一步增强它的作用。 4. This evidence reinforces my view that he is a spy. 这个证据证实了我认为他是间谍的这一看法。', '形容词: reinforceable');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shy', '[ʃaɪ]', 'adj.腼腆的；胆怯的；害羞的', '1. He was too shy to talk to anyone at the party. 在晚会上他很腼腆，没有和任何人讲话。 2. He only saw her sweet, shy face. 他只注意到她的甜甜的、腼腆的脸。 3. We must not fight shy of hard work. 我们不应回避艰苦的工作。 4. The shy girl was afraid to contradict. 这个害羞的女孩不敢提出反驳意见。', '副词: shyly 比较级: shier/shyer 最高级: shiest/shyest 名词: shyer 名词复数: shies 过去式: shied 过去分词: shied 现在分词: shying 第三人称单数: shies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impunity', '[ɪm\'pjuːnəti]', 'n.不受惩罚；免罚', '1. One cannot commit crimes with impunity. 一个人不能犯了罪不受惩罚。 2. The days of impunity seem to be over. 免受惩罚的日子似乎已经完结。', '名词复数: impunities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feeble', '[\'fiːbl]', 'adj.虚弱的；无力的', '1. The bishop said it with a feeble voice as he woke. 主教醒过来，用虚弱的声音说出。 2. Feeble and uncertain securities were thrown upon the market. 虚弱的或者没有把握的证券都向市场抛售了。 3. Tighter credit conditions are sapping already feeble demand. 紧缩的信贷让本就无力的需求更加乏力。 4. He bleated out a feeble excuse. 他以微弱的声音作无力的辩解。', '副词: feebly 比较级: feebler 最高级: feeblest 名词: feebleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prudent', '[\'pruːdnt]', 'adj.谨慎的；有远见的；精明的', '1. Young as he was, he was prudent. 他虽然如此年轻，却很慎重。 2. We should be modest and prudent. 我们应该谦虚谨慎。 3. Prudent man always fits his standard of living to his budget. 谨慎的人总是使他的生活水平符合他的收支预算。 4. It\'s prudent to take a thick coat in cold weather when you go out. 在寒冷的天气下外出时带上件厚外套是谨慎的。', '副词: prudently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assumption', '[ə\'sʌmpʃn]', 'n.假定；设想；担任(职责等)；假装', '1. The project was predicated on the assumption that the economy was expanding. 这一计划是以经济发展的设想为依据的。 2. The theory is based on a series of wrong assumptions. 这一理论是以一系列错误的设想为依据的。 3. His assumption of power was welcomed by everyone. 他的当权为大家所欢迎。 4. He talked with an assumption of ease. 他装出从容的样子说话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('haphazard', '[hæp\'hæzərd]', 'adj.偶然的；随意的；杂乱无章的 adv.杂乱地；任意地 n.偶然', '1. Meetings occurred in a somewhat haphazard fashion. 会见是以多少有点偶然的方式进行的。 2. I don\'t like the haphazard way he does things. 我不喜欢他随意的办事方式。 3. Why did you put the volumes of the encyclopedia in haphazard order? 你为何把这套百科全书放得杂乱无章? 4. It is just a thing done at haphazard. 这只是件偶然为之的事情。', '副词: haphazardly 名词: haphazardness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eventual', '[ɪ\'ventʃuəl]', 'adj.最终的；可能的', '1. The eventual decision came at last. 最终的决定出来了。 2. We must consider the eventual results. 我们必须考虑到最终的结果。 3. I fervently believe in our eventual victory. 我坚信我们最后会胜利。 4. His foolish behavior led to his eventual failure. 他的愚蠢行为导致了他最后的失败。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('voluntary', '[\'vɑːlənteri]', 'adj.自愿的；志愿的 n.(教堂礼拜仪式前后或进行期间的)乐器独奏', '1. He made a voluntary statement to the police. 他自愿为警方作供。 2. Many social services are still provided by voluntary societies in our city. 在我们的城市，许多社会服务仍然是有志愿团体提供的。 3. We rely entirely on voluntary contribution. 我们全靠自愿捐赠。 4. She\'s very taken up with voluntary work at the moment. 她目前大部分时间和精力都用在志愿工作上了。', '副词: voluntarily 名词: voluntariness 名词复数: voluntaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inclined', '[ɪn\'klaɪnd]', 'adj. 倾向于 ... 的', '1. He inclined to your opinion on that matter. 关于那个问题，他倾向于你的观点。 2. Most of us are inclined to the second view. 我们中间多数人都倾向于第二种看法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eliminate', '[ɪ\'lɪmɪneɪt]', 'v.除去；剔除；忽略；淘汰', '1. You must eliminate an unknown quantity. 你必须消去一个未知数。 2. Let us eliminate all uncertain on thought. 让我们从思想上消除一切疑惑。 3. We must eliminate unnecessary steps and get directly to the point. 我们必须忽略不必要的步骤,直接切入主题。 4. Their team was eliminated in the first round. 他们队在第一轮就被淘汰了。', '形容词: eliminative 名词: elimination 过去式: eliminated 过去分词: eliminated 现在分词: eliminating 第三人称单数: eliminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inert', '[ɪ\'nɜːrt]', 'adj.无行动的；惰性的；迟钝的', '1. She lay there inert, I thought she must be dead. 她躺在那儿一动不动，我想她一定是死了。 2. Stone is an inert mass of matter. 石头是一块无生命的物体。 3. Helium and neon are inert gases. 氦和氖为惰性气体。 4. He stood inert as the car came towards him. 汽车朝他开来时,他还呆呆地站著。', '副词: inertly 名词: inertness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abstraction', '[æb\'strækʃn]', 'n.抽象；抽象概念；心不在焉', '1. The idea of redness is an abstraction. 红色概念是一种抽象概念。 2. Maximize abstraction to maximize stability. 最大的抽象化以达到最大的稳定性。 3. The idea of redness is an abstraction. 红色概念是一种抽象概念。 4. Until now, our generation only knew war as an abstraction. 战争对于我们今天的这一代人仅仅是个抽象概念。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('innumerable', '[ɪ\'nuːmərəbl]', 'adj.无数的；数不清的', '1. Human beings once created innumerable miracles. 人类曾经创造了无数的奇迹。 2. Stars resemble innumerable dots of lights in the night sky. 夜空中，星星象无数的小亮点。 3. There are innumerable constellations in the sky. 天空中有数不清的星座。 4. Innumerable small shops presented a collection of cheap plastic goods. 数不清的小商店里陈列着一批廉价的塑料制品。', '副词: innumerably 名词: innumerableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('monotonous', '[mə\'nɑːtənəs]', 'adj.单调的', '1. The preacher\'s monotonous voice put me to sleep. 传教士单调的声音催我入眠。 2. His monotonous whistling grated on her nerves. 他单调的口哨声令她的神经受不了。', '副词: monotonously 名词: monotonousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('melodie', '[meɪlɒ\'diː]', '[法][音]小旋律歌曲', '1. O my luve is like the melodie That\'s sw... 大部分作品用苏格兰本土方言写成。 2. Cea mai noua melodie a farmatiei Linkin Park. andreylove 发起了一个话题: Linkin Park. 3. O my luve is like the melodie, That\\\'s sweetly played in tune. 啊，我的爱人象一支乐曲，乐声美妙、悠扬。 4. O my luve’s like the melodie That’s sweetly played in tune. /吾爱吾爱红玫瑰， 六月初开韵晓风；', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laudable', '[\'lɔːdəbl]', 'adj.值得称赞的', '1. Her work for charity is highly laudable. 她的慈善工作值得高度赞扬. 2. It\'s highly laudable and exemplary a thing as it is held to be. 这正如所认为的那样是一件值得高度称赞和仿效的事情。', '副词: laudably 名词: laudability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intensive', '[ɪn\'tensɪv]', 'adj.密集的；彻底的；精细的；强调的 n.(语法)强调成份', '1. This patient requires intensive care. 该病人需要加强护理。 2. We concentrated intensive fire on the enemy. 我们集中密集的火力向敌人攻击。 3. An intensive search failed to reveal any clues. 经过彻底搜查未发现任何线索。 4. Do you have an intensive reading of English this term? 这个学期你们有英语精读课程吗？', '副词: intensively 名词: intensiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adjust', '[ə\'dʒʌst]', 'v.调整；校准；调节；使适应', '1. Could you teach me how to adjust the iris of the camera? 你能教我怎么调照相机的光圈吗？ 2. This kind of desk can be adjusted to the height you need. 这种书桌的高低可以按照你的需要调节。 3. He can\'t adjust himself to the whirl of modern life in this big city. 他无法适应这个大都市的现代生活的忙碌。 4. Over the years, we all learned to adjust, to become more comfortable with each other, and to adapt to our new family arrangement. 年复一年，我们都学会了调整自己，学会了彼此宽容，学会了适应我们新的家庭规则。', '形容词: adjustable 副词: adjustably 名词: adjuster 过去式: adjusted 过去分词: adjusted 现在分词: adjusting 第三人称单数: adjusts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('curriculum', '[kə\'rɪkjələm]', 'n.全部课程；课程', '1. Our curriculum comprises Politics, Chinese, English and History. 我们的课程共有四门：政治、汉语、英语、历史。 2. Our mathematics curriculum is much more complicated now. 我们的数学课现在复杂得多了。', '形容词: curricular 名词复数: curricula');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gigantic', '[dʒaɪ\'ɡæntɪk]', 'adj.巨大的', '1. The new airplane looked like a gigantic bird. 这架新飞机看起来像一只巨大的鸟。 2. City is abstracted into several gigantic buildings. 城市，被抽象化为几个巨大的建筑物。', '副词: gigantically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decadence', '[\'dekədəns]', 'n.衰落；颓废', '1. The decadence of morals is bad for nation. 道德的堕落对于国家是不利的。 2. But even your dreams will be but a pale shadow of my true decadence. 但你的梦不过是我真实衰落中一个苍白的影子罢了。 3. In time, the foul odor of Roman decadence would grow harder to disguise. 时日一到，罗马矫饰的颓废气味终将难以遮掩。 4. It embraced a decadence and an abandon that set it apart from the rest of Egypt. 这里拥抱着某种颓废和狂放，让它有别于埃及的其它地方。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dagger', '[\'dæɡər]', 'n.短剑；匕首；[印]剑号', '1. He parried the sword with his dagger. 他用短剑挡开了马刀。 2. Put the dagger back in its sheath. 把短剑插回鞘内。 3. The hoodlum stabbed at me with a dagger. 小流氓用匕首向我刺来。 4. The kind whisper went to my heart like a dagger. 这仁慈的低语象一把匕首直刺进我的心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('character', '[\'kærəktər]', 'n.个性；品质；字符；人物；名誉；地位 adj.[剧](角色)代表某一特性的', '1. The boy has a strong character. 这孩子个性很强。 2. He is remembered for the nobility of his character. 他因品质高尚而被人怀念。 3. We need only keep track of the last marked character. 我们只要记住最后标记的字符。 4. I never saw a character so thoroughly hit off . 我从没看见过一个人物被描写得如此淋漓尽致。', '形容词: characterless 过去式: charactered 过去分词: charactered 现在分词: charactering 第三人称单数: characters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defect', '[\'diːfekt]', 'n.缺点；缺陷 vi.背叛', '1. If it were not for this defect, I shall hire him at once. 如果不是因为这个缺点，我会马上雇用他。 2. The new car had to be withdrawn from the market because of a mechanical defect. 那种新汽车因有机械缺陷只好撤出市场。 3. We thought that his troops might defect. 我们认为他的部队会叛变。', '名词: defection 过去式: defected 过去分词: defected 现在分词: defecting 第三人称单数: defects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dead', '[ded]', 'adj.死的；不起作用的；无趣的；筋疲力尽的；麻木的；完全的；无效的；沉闷的；（指球）界外的 adv.完全地；直接地；突然地', '1. It lay there with its eyes closed, dead as a doornail. 它躺在那里眼睛闭著，确实死了。 2. He has been dead for two years. 他已死了两年。 3. The phone went dead. 电话打不通了。 4. The battery is dead. 电瓶没电了。 5. He was dead asleep. 他酣然大睡。', '比较级: deader 最高级: deadest 名词: deadness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proliferate', '[prə\'lɪfəreɪt]', 'v.繁殖；增生；使 ... 激增；使 ... 扩散', '1. Microbes proliferate rapidly. 微生物繁殖迅速。 2. Health food shops proliferate in this region. 保健食品店在这个地区增加了。 3. Fantasies proliferate where facts are few. 事实缺乏则幻想增多。 4. Dishonest vendors proliferate, forcing true entrepreneurs out of the industry. 无信用的小商贩激增,将好企业从行业中驱赶出来。', '形容词: proliferative 名词: proliferation 过去式: proliferated 过去分词: proliferated 现在分词: proliferating 第三人称单数: proliferates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('miser', '[\'maɪzər]', 'n.守财奴；吝啬鬼', '1. Soon Mary discovered she had married a miser. 不久，玛丽发现她嫁给了一个守财奴。 2. The miser gloated over his gold. 守财奴心满意足地望着他的金子。 3. The selfish old miser had a cold nature. 这个自私的老吝啬鬼生性冷酷。 4. That miser told over his money every night. 那个吝啬鬼每天晚上都要把他的钱数一遍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glaring', '[\'ɡlerɪŋ]', 'adj.耀眼的；华丽而俗气的；明显的；怒视的 动词glare的现在分词.', '1. The street was bone dry and glaring white. 马路上一个水点也没有，干巴巴的发着些白光。 2. His pallid skin was sensitive to the glaring sun. 他苍白的皮肤对耀眼的阳光很敏感。 3. There is such rich color in her cheeks and lips that make-up would be glaring and would cheapen her appearance. 她的双颊和嘴唇颜色鲜丽，再用化妆品就会显得俗气刺眼。 4. The report is full of glaring errors. 那份报告满是显而易见的错误。', '副词: glaringly 名词: glaringness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inconvenient', '[ˌɪnkən\'viːniənt]', 'adj.不方便的', '1. He came at an inconvenient time. 他在不方便的时候来了。 2. Come, if it is not inconvenient to you. 要是没有什么不方便的话，就请来吧。', '副词: inconveniently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('passionate', '[\'pæʃənət]', 'adj.热情的；激情的；易怒的', '1. His passionate speech had an effect on our emotions. 他的热情的演讲打动了我们的感情。 2. She is a passionate advocate of education reform. 她是一名教育改革的热情拥护者。 3. He made a passionate speech about the sufferings of the poor. 他就穷人的苦难做了一个充满激情的演讲。 4. His early experience turn him into a passionate social reformer. 他早年的经历使他变成了一个狂热的社会改革者。', '副词: passionately 名词: passionateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meander', '[mi\'ændər]', 'v.缓慢而弯曲地流动；漫步；闲聊 n.河流的曲折；漫步；迂回曲折的进程', '1. They tumble down mountainsides; they meander through flat farmlands. 它们滚滚冲下山脊，蜿蜒穿过平坦的农田。 2. I liked to meander through familiar streets. 我喜欢闲逛穿过熟悉的街道。 3. They usually meander down to the pub after work. 他们通常下班后漫步到那家小酒店去。 4. The discussion meandered (on) for hours. 讨论会漫无边际地进行了几小时。 5. Major changes in a river course result in both lateral shifts of the old meander belt and in the development of new belts. 河道中大的变动，造成老河曲带的侧向迁移和新河曲带的产生。', '形容词: meandrous 副词: meanderingly 名词: meanderer 过去式: meandered 过去分词: meandered 现在分词: meandering 第三人称单数: meanders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('protrude', '[proʊ\'truːd]', 'v.突出；伸出', '1. Helen\' s teeth protrude too far. 海伦的牙齿太突出了。 2. It made his great nose protrude more arrogantly. 这就使得他的大鼻子更加傲慢地翘起来。 3. He is hurt by a shelf protruding from the wall. 他被一个从墙上伸出的架子伤着了。 4. He managed to hang on to a piece of rock protruding from the cliff. 他设法抓住了悬崖上向外伸出的岩石。', '形容词: protrudent 过去式: protruded 过去分词: protruded 现在分词: protruding 第三人称单数: protrudes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enzyme', '[\'enzaɪm]', 'n.酶', '1. Nitrate reductase is a short-lived enzyme. 硝酸还原酶是短寿酶。 2. Thermodynamics of transient enzyme kinetics. 瞬时酶动态热力学。', '形容词: enzymatic 副词: enzymatically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('traverse', '[trə\'vɜːrs]', 'n.横贯；横木 v.横贯；穿越；详细讨论；阻止；否认；【计】遍历', '1. The railway traverses hundreds of miles of desert. 这条铁路贯穿数百英里的沙漠。 2. The traverse across the country will be long and arduous. 穿越这个国家将是漫长而又艰苦的旅程。 3. The traverse in the room was easily seen from the doorway. 从门口看过去，很容易看见房间门窗的横档。 4. The railway traverses hundreds of miles of desert. 这条铁路贯穿数百英里的沙漠。', '形容词: traversable 名词: traversal 过去式: traversed 过去分词: traversed 现在分词: traversing 第三人称单数: traverses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('modify', '[\'mɑːdɪfaɪ]', 'v.修改；更改；缓和；修饰', '1. We have to modify our plan a little bit. 我们得对我们的计划稍加修改。 2. The policy was agreed by the committee, but only in a modified form. 那项政策经修改后才获得委员会同意。 3. The union has been forced to slightly modify its position. 工会被迫稍稍改变立场。 4. He\'ll have to modify his views if he wants to be elected. 他要想当选就得把观点改得缓和些。', '形容词: modifiable 名词: modifiability 过去式: modified 过去分词: modified 现在分词: modifying 第三人称单数: modifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barricade', '[ˌbærɪ\'keɪd]', 'n.【C】路障；街垒；障碍物；栅栏 n.(常用复数形式)barricades:有激烈争论的领域或议题 vt.设路障挡住；阻拦；封锁', '1. Please step behind the police barricade. 请站在警戒线之后。 2. The soldiers make a barricade across the road. 士兵在路上设路障。 3. The soldiers stormed the barricades erected by the rioting crowd. 士兵们向暴乱分子设置的街垒发起了猛攻。 4. Everyone should be guarded by legal barricades. 人人都应受法律保障。 5. Residents were ready to go to the barricades to fight the school closure. 居民关于反对学校关闭一事准备展开争论。 6. They barricaded the main road with fallen trees. 他们用倒下的树堵住了主要道路。', '名词: barricader 过去式: barricaded 过去分词: barricaded 现在分词: barricading 第三人称单数: barricades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('digress', '[daɪ\'ɡres]', 'v.走向岔道；离开本题；扯到枝节上', '1. I\'ll tell you a funny story,if I may digress for a moment. 如果我可以暂时离开一下话题，我将讲一个有趣的故事给你听。 2. Don\'t digress from the subject when lecturing. 讲课时不要扯到枝节上。', '过去式: digressed 过去分词: digressed 现在分词: digressing 第三人称单数: digresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evasion', '[ɪ\'veɪʒn]', 'n.逃避；躲避；借口', '1. The senate was censured for income tax evasion. 这名参议员因逃避缴纳所得税而受到指责。 2. The senate was censured for income tax evasion . 这名参议员因逃避缴纳所得税而受到指责。 3. The fox\'s clever evasion of the dogs. 狐狸狡猾地躲避狗。 4. Voters are tired of listening to lies and evasions. 选举人厌倦了谎言和借口。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sauce', '[sɔːs]', 'n.酱汁；调味汁；<口>无礼 vt.给 ... 调味；使 ... 增加趣味；对 ... 无礼', '1. Waiter, may I have steak sauce, please？ 服务生,请给我一些牛排酱汁。 2. The sauce is thin and tasteless. 这酱汁淡而无味。 3. The cook poured the sauce over the food. 厨师将调味汁倒在食物上。 4. The secret of this dish is in the sauce. 这道菜好吃的秘诀在于调味汁。 5. He sauced criticism with flattery 他用谄媚来冲淡批评。', '过去式: sauced 过去分词: sauced 现在分词: saucing 第三人称单数: sauces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foment', '[foʊ\'ment]', 'v.煽动；引发；激起；[医]热敷', '1. His word finally foment her hostility. 他的言词终于引发了她的敌意。', '名词: fomenter 过去式: fomented 过去分词: fomented 现在分词: fomenting 第三人称单数: foments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disdain', '[dɪs\'deɪn]', 'n.轻蔑 v.蔑视', '1. Laval brushed this aside with disdain. 赖伐尔以轻蔑的态度拒绝了。 2. The receptionist looked at me with disdain when I walked into Suffolk College asking to enrol. 当我走进萨克福大学，要求报读时，接待员用轻蔑的眼神看着我。 3. He disdained that man for snobbishness and was unwilling to talk to him. 他鄙视那个势利小人，不愿和他说话。', '过去式: disdained 过去分词: disdained 现在分词: disdaining 第三人称单数: disdains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allergy', '[\'ælərdʒi]', 'n.过敏症；反感；厌恶', '1. I have an allergy to penicillin. 我对青霉素有过敏反应。 2. Some people have an allergy to pollen. 一些人对花粉有过敏反应。 3. She has an allergy to cocktail parties. 她讨厌参加鸡尾酒会。 4. He has an allergy to wine. 他极讨厌酒。', '名词复数: allergies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sculpture', '[\'skʌlptʃər]', 'n.雕塑；雕刻 v.雕刻；雕塑；刻蚀；当雕刻师', '1. He was a professor of sculpture at the Academy. 他在学院是一位雕塑教授。 2. The smooth contour of the sculpture is wonderful. 雕塑物平滑的轮廓线简直太美了。 3. She studied sculpture at art school. 她在美术学校学习雕刻。 4. There are two horses sculptured in bronze at the gate. 在大门口有两匹用青铜雕塑的马。', '形容词: sculptural 副词: sculpturally 过去式: sculptured 过去分词: sculptured 现在分词: sculpturing 第三人称单数: sculptures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adjoin', '[ə\'dʒɔɪn]', 'v.邻接；毗连', '1. We heard laughter in the adjoining room. 我们听到了邻屋的笑声。 2. The playing field adjoins the school. 体育场紧靠着学校。 3. Our house adjoins theirs. 我们的房屋与他们的毗连。', '过去式: adjoined 过去分词: adjoined 现在分词: adjoining 第三人称单数: adjoins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('homogeneous', '[ˌhoʊmə\'dʒiːniəs]', 'adj.同质的；同种的；相似的', '1. Life in the United States is no longer if it ever was culturally homogeneous. 美国的生活已经不再是，如果它曾经是，同源文化。 2. Japan has a largely homogeneous population. 日本的人口基本上同属一 个种族。 3. More of the hitherto homogeneous societies are becoming plural ones. 越来越多的单一种族社会逐渐变得多元化。', '副词: homogeneously 名词: homogeneousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hummingbird', '[ˈhʌmɪŋbɜːd]', 'n.蜂鸟', '1. A hummingbird is poising over the flower. 一只蜂鸟在花上盘旋。 2. Have you ever seen a hummingbird? 你见过蜂鸟没？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coil', '[kɔɪl]', 'n.卷；圈；线圈 v.盘绕；卷成圈', '1. He passed me a coil of thread. 他递给我一卷线。 2. The birds are entangled in the coil of a net. 鸟被缠在网圈里了。 3. The burnt coil should be renewed. 烧穿的线圈应换新的。 4. This is a double induction coil. 这是一对感应线圈。 5. The snake coiled itself around the tree. 蛇盘绕在树上。', '名词: coiler 过去式: coiled 过去分词: coiled 现在分词: coiling 第三人称单数: coils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thrust', '[θrʌst]', 'v.刺；插入；推挤 n.刺；推力；要旨', '1. The mugger thrust at his victim with a knife. 抢劫者用刀子向受害人刺去。 2. The murderer killed her by thrusting a knife in her back. 凶手把刀刺进她的背部，杀害了她。 3. He thrust his hands into his pockets. 他把两手插入衣袋里。 4. We thrust our way through the crowd. 我们用力挤过人群。 5. The fencer parried his opponent\'s thrust. 击剑手挡开了对手的猛刺。', '形容词: thrustful 名词: thruster 过去式: thrust 过去分词: thrust 现在分词: thrusting 第三人称单数: thrusts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('loathe', '[loʊð]', 'v.厌恶；憎恶', '1. You know how I loathe typing and shorthand. 你知道我多么讨厌打字和速记。 2. I loathe people who spread malicious gossip. 我讨厌那些散布充满恶意的流言蜚语的人。 3. I value copyright. I loathe its abuse. 我重视版权，我憎恶版权被滥用。', '名词: loather 过去式: loathed 过去分词: loathed 现在分词: loathing 第三人称单数: loathes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legalize', '[\'liːɡəlaɪz]', 'vt.使合法化；法律上认为正当 =legalise（英）', '1. Some people want to legalize the possession of cannabis. 有些人想将私有大麻合法化。 2. They won\'t ever legalize the drugs trade. 他们永远不会把毒品的行业合法化的。', '名词: legalization 过去式: legalized 过去分词: legalized 现在分词: legalizing 第三人称单数: legalizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('howl', '[haʊl]', 'n.长嚎；高声叫喊；啸鸣 v.嚎叫；大声哭；吼叫着说出', '1. The howl seemed to freeze the world with fear. 那嚎叫声好像要令整个世界毛骨悚然。 2. You can grip the club when you hear the wolf howl. 听见狼嚎你可以握紧棍子。 3. A sudden howl pierced the silence. 突然一声嗥叫划破了寂静。 4. They listened to the howl of the wind through the trees. 他们听着风在林间呼啸的声音。 5. The dog howled over its master\'s body. 狗对着主人的尸体哀嚎。', '过去式: howled 过去分词: howled 现在分词: howling 第三人称单数: howls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solid', '[\'sɑːlɪd]', 'adj.固体的；实心的；结实的；可靠的 n.固体；立体图形 adv.一致地', '1. Ice is water in solid state. 冰是水的固体状态。 2. In fact, it was originally a solid rock. 其实,这本来是实心的岩石。 3. All these have laid a solid political foundation for consolidated national unity. 所有这些为巩固国家统一奠定了坚实的政治基础。 4. You should present solid evidence to prove your point. 你应该提供有说服力的证据来证明你的观点。 5. Water becomes solid when it freezes. 水结冰时便变成固体。', '副词: solidly 比较级: solider 最高级: solidest 名词: solidness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grease', '[ɡriːs]', 'n.油脂 vt.用油脂涂；上油；贿赂', '1. Mother smeared grease on her hands. 母亲用油脂涂沫了双手。 2. The engine was covered in grease. 发动机上有层油脂。 3. I use the floor cleaner to remove grease. 我用地板除垢剂清除油污。 4. You\'re supposed to grease the pan first. 你应该先往锅里加点儿油。', '形容词: greaseless 过去式: greased 过去分词: greased 现在分词: greasing 第三人称单数: greases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('girder', '[\'ɡɜːrdər]', 'n.[建]大梁', '1. The girder was clinched into the wall. 大梁被钉牢在墙中。 2. I saw with my own eyes a girder fall and crush him to death. 我眼瞅着一根大梁掉下来把他砸死了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dampen', '[\'dæmpən]', 'v.(使)潮湿；使沮丧；抑制', '1. Please dampen that sponge for me. 请把那海绵弄湿了给我。 2. The camp supplies dampened during the long rainy season. 营地补给品在漫长的雨季里变潮湿了。 3. The bad news dampened our spirits. 这恶耗使得我们精神沮丧。 4. Nothing can dampen my spirit and darken my life. 没有什么能使我沮丧，使我生活暗淡。', '名词: dampener 过去式: dampened 过去分词: dampened 现在分词: dampening 第三人称单数: dampens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('snowflake', '[\'snoʊfleɪk]', 'n.雪花；雪片', '1. No snowflake ever falls in the wrong place. 没有雪花落到不该落的地方。 2. I caught the first snowflake of winter! 我得到了冬天里的第一片雪花！ 3. Each snowflake has its own unique pattern. 每一个雪花都拥有自己的独有图案而从不重覆的。 4. Can you feel a snowflake\'s dancing in the air? 你能感觉到雪花的漫天飞舞吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irritate', '[\'ɪrɪteɪt]', 'v.激怒；使疼痛或发炎', '1. His letter irritated me a little. 他的信使我有点恼怒。 2. Don\'t irritate her, she\'s on a short fuse today. 别惹她，她今天动不动就发火。 3. Wool irritates my skin. 毛织物会使我的皮肤过敏。 4. Insect bites irritate your skin. 虫子叮疼了你的皮肤。', '副词: irritatingly 名词: irritator 过去式: irritated 过去分词: irritated 现在分词: irritating 第三人称单数: irritates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gull', '[ɡʌl]', 'n.鸥；易受骗之人 v.诈欺；骗', '1. Gull flies over the sea. 海鸥在大海上飞翔。 2. The wings of the sea gull were beating frantically. 海鸥的翅膀在疯狂地扑扇着。 3. Only Merlin would seek to gull me so, even though he should know better. 只有梅林会这样引我上当，他很明白这个道理。 4. It\'s wrong to gull a child. 欺骗孩子是不对的。', '过去式: gulled 过去分词: gulled 现在分词: gulling 第三人称单数: gulls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shade', '[ʃeɪd]', 'n.阴影；遮蔽；遮光物；(色彩的)浓淡 vt.遮蔽；使阴暗；使渐变；略减（价格） vi.渐变', '1. This artist uses shade to good effect. 这位画家有效地利用阴影。 2. There are no trees or bushes to give shade. 没有树木或灌木丛可以遮荫。 3. Something,such as a window shade or a Venetian blind,that hinders vision or shuts out light. 遮光物如窗帘或软百叶窗等能遮挡视线或挡住阳光的物体。 4. The portrait shows fine effects of light and shade. 这幅肖像画的浓淡色调表现得很好。 5. He tried to shade his house with thick trees. 他想让这些大树把房子遮住。 6. The colors of the light shaded from blue into purple. 光线的颜色由蓝逐渐变紫。', '名词: shader 过去式: shaded 过去分词: shaded 现在分词: shading 第三人称单数: shades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mutual', '[\'mjuːtʃuəl]', 'adj.共同的；相互的', '1. Other organizations have joined the confederation for mutual benefit. 其他组织为了共同的利益也加入了这个联盟。 2. My friend and I have mutual enthusiasm for music. 我和我的朋友对音乐有着共同的爱好。 3. Let\'s give mutual support and inspiration to each other. 让我们互相支持，互相鼓励。 4. Language differences are often a barrier to mutual understanding. 语言不同,常常阻碍到彼此的了解。', '副词: mutually 名词: mutuality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tactic', '[\'tæktɪk]', 'n.战略；策略', '1. The new tactic was put into operation early in 1939. 这个新的战略是在1939年初开始运用的。 2. The team won the game thanks to Jeff\'s fabulous spot tactic. 多亏了杰夫当场制定的英明战略，他的球队赢了。 3. Reducing prices is a common sales tactic. 降价是常用的销售策略。 4. Confrontation is not always the best tactic. 对抗并非总是上策。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('temperature', '[\'temprətʃər]', 'n.气温；体温；温度；发烧', '1. The temperature has stayed hot this week. 本周气温一直都很热。 2. The temperature soared to 43 degrees centigrade on July 25. 7月25日,气温猛升到4摄氏度。 3. After the storm there will be a sharp drop in temperature. 风暴过后,气温会骤降。 4. Let me take his (her) temperature and have a check. 我来给他(她)量一下体温,检查一下。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('poise', '[pɔɪz]', 'n.平衡；姿态；镇静 v.使 ... 平衡；保持 ... 姿势；做准备；盘旋', '1. Good poise is important for a dancer. 保持良好的平衡对舞蹈演员非常重要。 2. He discovers true poise and equilibrium. 他明白了什么是真正的平静和平衡。 3. We admired the graceful poise of the dancer. 我们很欣赏那位舞蹈演员的优美舞姿。 4. She was a beautiful girl with the grace and poise of a natural model. 她是一个美丽的姑娘，有着模特儿的那种优雅姿态。 5. He poised the glass on the shelf. 他把玻璃杯稳稳地放在架子上。', '过去式: poised 过去分词: poised 现在分词: poising 第三人称单数: poises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('doubt', '[daʊt]', 'n.怀疑；疑惑；悬而未定 vt.怀疑；不信任 vi.不确定', '1. There is no doubt that we will be successful. 毫无疑问我们会成功的。 2. Although a very religious man, he is still troubled by occasional doubts. 他虽然笃信宗教，但有时仍感到迷惘。 3. The outcome of this discussion is still in doubt. 这次讨论的结果还未定。 4. She\'s been feeling ill these days, so I doubt that she\'ll feel up to going to the country this weekend. 她最近一直都不舒服,所以我怀疑周末她是否能到乡下去。 5. She said that I was getting into the habit of doubting. 她说我渐渐地好像对什么都不确定。', '名词: doubter 过去式: doubted 过去分词: doubted 现在分词: doubting 第三人称单数: doubts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rayon', '[\'reɪɑːn]', 'n.人造丝；人造纤维', '1. Silk is distinct from rayon in every respect. 在各个方面真丝跟人造丝截然不同。 2. Rayon rank second only to cotton as the most widely used fiber. 人造丝是仅次于棉花的使用得最广泛的织物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('release', '[rɪ\'liːs]', 'n.释放；让渡；发行 vt.释放；让与；准予发表；发射', '1. The prisoner was questioned before his release. 囚犯被释放之前受到了审问。 2. The puffball is ready to release its spores. 尘菌已经要释放孢子了。 3. The electrons in the upper band eventually release energy, thereby emitting photons. 上层能带中的电子最后会发射光子释放能量。', '过去式: released 过去分词: released 现在分词: releasing 第三人称单数: releases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('generally', '[\'dʒenrəli]', 'adv.一般地；通常；普遍地', '1. Generally speaking, women live longer than men. 一般而言，女性寿命较男性长。 2. It is generally accepted that smoking is harmful to our health. 吸烟有害健康，这是大家公认的。 3. Generally, we go to the sea for our holidays. 我们通常到海边度假。 4. He generally keeps silent at a meeting. 他通常在会上保持沉默。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equate', '[i\'kweɪt]', 'v.同等看待；等同；使相等', '1. He equates poverty with misery. 他认为贫穷就是不幸。 2. You can\'t equate the education system of Britain to that of Germany. 不能把英国教育制度与德国教育制度等同起来。 3. We must not equate thrift with stinginess. 我们不能把勤俭和吝啬等同起来。 4. It \'s impossible to equate wealth and happiness . 财富与幸福无法等同。', '过去式: equated 过去分词: equated 现在分词: equating 第三人称单数: equates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('porous', '[\'pɔːrəs]', 'adj.可渗透的；多孔的', '1. We need to watch our plants so we become attuned to their needs, but small pots dry out faster than big ones and porous clay pots dry out faster than plastic ones. 我们必须经常观察我们的植物，这样才能了解它们的需要，但要注意小罐子比大罐子干透的时间更快，可渗透的粘土罐也比塑料罐子干透的时间更快。 2. Most soils and rocks are porous. 大部分土壤和岩石都是多孔的。 3. Oxford is a rather soft and porous cotton fabric. 牛浸布是一种颇为柔软，多孔的棉织物。', '副词: porously 名词: porousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('illuminate', '[ɪ\'luːmɪneɪt]', 'vt.照明；阐释；说明', '1. plastic food 2. A sudden smile illuminated her face. 突然的微笑使她容光焕发。 3. Footnotes illuminate the difficult passage of the book. 脚注中解释了书中许多难懂的道理。 4. Our interesting teacher could illuminate almost any subject we studied. 我们这位有趣的老师几乎能解释清楚我们所学的所有科目。', '副词: illuminatingly 过去式: illuminated 过去分词: illuminated 现在分词: illuminating 第三人称单数: illuminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('informal', '[ɪn\'fɔːrml]', 'adj.非正式的；不拘形式的', '1. These words are informal. 这些词是非正式用语。 2. We had an informal meeting. 我们做了非正式的会晤。 3. Once a week we have an informal wine tasting. 我们一周有一次非正式的品酒活动。 4. An informal work setting helps to build employee enthusiasm and morale. 不拘形式的工作环境，提高了员工的热情与士气。', '副词: informally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shabby', '[\'ʃæbi]', 'adj.破旧的；寒酸的；低劣的，无耻的；卑劣的', '1. He owns nothing beyond the shabby house. 除了那个破旧的房子,他一无所有。 2. His shabby appearance creates a bad impression. 他那寒酸的样子给人留下不好的印象。 3. She is none the less beautiful for her shabby clothing. 即使她衣衫褴褛，却仍然美丽。 4. His reasoning is weak, even shabby. 他的论证软弱无力，甚至可以说很拙劣。', '副词: shabbily 比较级: shabbier 最高级: shabbiest 名词: shabbiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exhume', '[ɪɡ\'zuːm]', 'v.掘出(尸体以检验)；发掘', '1. When the police exhumed the corpse they discovered traces of poison in it. 警方掘出尸体，发现有中毒的痕迹。 2. He\'s going to ask authorization to exhume the body and have it put somewhere else. 他去请求许可将死者的尸体掘出，移到别的地方。 3. They exhumed for days, but did not find anything. 他们发掘了几天，但什么都没有找到。', '名词: exhumation 过去式: exhumed 过去分词: exhumed 现在分词: exhuming 第三人称单数: exhumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('graph', '[ɡræf]', 'n.图表；示意图 vt.(以图表)表示', '1. The graph shows a bulge in the price of meat. 图表显示肉类价格上涨。 2. Our research results are displayed in the form of a graph. 我们的研究结果已用图表列出. 3. This is a simple graph of legislative process. 这是立法过程的简易示意图。 4. This program provides a simple way to graph the flow chart. 这个程序提供了一种简单的方式用图表示流程图。', '过去式: graphed 过去分词: graphed 现在分词: graphing 第三人称单数: graphs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heresy', '[\'herəsi]', 'n.异端；异教；反面观点', '1. The book has a tincture of heresy. 这本书稍有异端意味。 2. He was sentenced to be guilty of heresy. 他被判犯有异端罪。 3. At this defiant heresy, Mammy\'s brow lowered with indignation. 听了这番不伦不类的犟话，嬷嬷烦恼得皱紧了眉头。 4. Every truth has geological strata,and you can\'t have an orthodoxy without a heresy. 每个真理都是有层次的，这世界没有错就没有对。', '名词复数: heresies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('splash', '[splæʃ]', 'n.溅泼（声）；溅泼的量；溅污的斑点；骚动；少许 v.溅（湿）；报道', '1. There was splash in the pond, and a big goldfish bobbed up. 水池里扑通一声，一条大金鱼窜了起来。 2. He jumped into the water with a splash. 他噗通一声跳进水里。 3. There\'s a splash of paint on the white wall. 白墙上溅上了一片油漆。 4. He achieved a perfectly clean entry,and there is almost no splash. 他的入水非常漂亮，几乎没有溅起水花。 5. The boys always splash about in rainwater. 孩子们总是在雨水里玩耍。', '名词: splasher 过去式: splashed 过去分词: splashed 现在分词: splashing 第三人称单数: splashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rubbish', '[\'rʌbɪʃ]', 'n.垃圾；废物；废话；碎屑 v.贬损', '1. The dustman comes once a week to collect the rubbish. 垃圾工每周来收一次垃圾。 2. That new TV show is absolutely rubbish. 那个新的电视节目一点儿价值都没有。 3. He was gulled into buying rubbish. 他被骗买了废物。 4. I thought he talked a lot of rubbish. 我觉得他谈的都是些废话。 5. The film was rubbished by the critics. 影评家把这部影片贬得一无是处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discount', '[\'dɪskaʊnt]', 'n.折扣；贴现率 vt.打折扣；贴现；不全信；不重视 vi.贴现；减息贷款', '1. These goods will be sold at a discount. 这些货物将减价出售。 2. We give 10 percent discount for cash. 现金付款，我们九折优惠。 3. The discount rate is set by the Fed. 贴现率是由联储决定的。 4. The preferred project in this case depends on the discount rate, not the IRR. 该例中，我们倾向选择哪个项目取决于贴现率，而不是内部收益率。 5. That store does not discount at all. 那家商店出售商品一概不打折。 6. We usually only discount acceptance trade and commercial bills. 我们通常只贴现已承兑的商业票据。', '形容词: discountable 过去式: discounted 过去分词: discounted 现在分词: discounting 第三人称单数: discounts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rhyme', '[raɪm]', 'n.韵；押韵；韵文 v.押韵；用韵诗表达', '1. Do you understand the rhyme of this poem? 你理解这首诗的韵吗? 2. Poetry often follows special patterns of rhyme. 诗歌常常遵循专门的节奏和押韵格式。 3. Shakespeare sometimes wrote in rhyme. 莎士比亚有时用韵文写作。 4. You can\'t rhyme “sleep”with “feet”. 你不能用“sleep”和“feet”押韵。', '过去式: rhymed/rimed 过去分词: rhymed/rimed 现在分词: rhyming/riming 第三人称单数: rhymes/rimes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('virtuous', '[\'vɜːrtʃuəs]', 'adj.有品德的；有德行的；贞洁的', '1. She always tried to lead a virtuous life. 她一直想要过一种高洁的生活。 2. My uncle is always proud of having a virtuous wife. 叔叔一直为娶到一位贤德的妻子而骄傲。 3. I do not know if she is virtuous, but she is ugly, and with a woman that is half the battle. 我不知道她以往是否贞洁,但她容貌丑陋,对一个女人来说,这等于大势已定了。', '副词: virtuously 名词: virtuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irresistible', '[ˌɪrɪ\'zɪstəbl]', 'adj.无法抗拒的', '1. The raging trend of reforms is irresistible. 改革浪潮是不可抗拒的。 2. Tito felt an irresistible desire to go up to her. 蒂托感到有一种无法克制的欲望，促使他到她的身边去。 3. He had an irresistible desire to run away. 他一心想逃跑,无法抑制这个愿望。 4. Historical trend is irresistible. 历史潮流是不可阻挡的。', '副词: irresistibly 名词: irresistibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dangerous', '[\'deɪndʒərəs]', 'adj.危险的；不安全的', '1. It is dangerous to walk on thin ice in a lake. 在湖中薄冰上行走是很危险的。 2. Dangerous driving should be severely punished. 危险驾驶应受严惩。 3. It is dangerous for you to stay here. 你呆在这儿不安全。', '副词: dangerously 名词: dangerousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('analyze', '[\'ænəlaɪz]', 'vt.分析；解析；研究', '1. Can you analyze the structure of the sentence for me? 你能给我分析一下这个句子的结构吗？ 2. Let\'s analyze the problem and see what went wrong. 让我们分析一下这道题，看什么地方出错了。 3. You should analyze the essence of the problem. 你应该剖析问题的实质。 4. They will take the problem apart and analyze it. 他们会深入剖析这个问题。', '形容词: analyzable 名词: analyzation 过去式: analyzed 过去分词: analyzed 现在分词: analyzing 第三人称单数: analyzes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exhilarating', '[ɪɡ\'zɪləreɪtɪŋ]', 'adj.令人振奋的；令人兴奋的；令人高兴的', '1. And it has been an exhilarating and eventful time. 这是一个令人激动的并且重要的时间。 2. I had more exhilarating fun coming back this summer than I had had before. 这个夏天的回归我所得到的振奋和乐趣远比以往为多。 3. Our first parachute jump was an exhilarating experience. 我们第一次跳伞感到兴奋莫名。 4. Jason: The most exhilarating day in my life. 杰森：今天是我一生中最最兴奋的日子。', '副词: exhilaratingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reduce', '[rɪ\'duːs]', 'v.减少；缩小；使落魄；简化；还原', '1. The new government\'s prime task is to reduce the level of inflation. 新政府的主要任务是减低通货膨胀的水平。 2. We need to reduce our dependence on oil as a source of energy. 在能源方面,我们需减少对石油的依赖。 3. We must gradually reduce the wage gap. 我们要逐步缩小工资差距。 4. They were reduced to begging. 他们沦落到得要饭。', '形容词: reducible 副词: reducibly 名词: reducer 过去式: reduced 过去分词: reduced 现在分词: reducing 第三人称单数: reduces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refuge', '[\'refjuːdʒ]', 'n.避难；避难所；庇护 v.庇护；避难', '1. They took refuge in a cave yesterday. 他们昨天是在一个洞里避难的。 2. It is a classic sanctuary in which the rationalist fancy may take refuge. 这是一所古雅的圣殿，理性主义者可以躲在其中。 3. A small cave was the only refuge from the cold. 小洞穴是唯一的避寒处。 4. They were forced to seek refuge from the fighting. 他们被迫寻求庇护，以躲避战争。 5. Drug traffickers refuged in these border areas. 毒品贩子在这些边界地区躲避。', '过去式: refuged 过去分词: refuged 现在分词: refuging 第三人称单数: refuges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fright', '[fraɪt]', 'n.惊骇；惊恐；<口>怪人', '1. Hearing the news, we turned pale with fright. 听到这消息后，我们惊骇失色。 2. Tom\'s fright weakened every muscle in his body. 汤姆所受的惊骇使他全身的肌肉都没有劲了。 3. He cried out in fright as the dark figure approached. 那个黑影向他逼近，他吓得叫了出来。 4. He gave me a fright by bursting into a sudden laughter. 他突然大笑起来，吓了我一跳。', '过去式: frighted 过去分词: frighted 现在分词: frighting 第三人称单数: frights');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crest', '[krest]', 'n.浪尖；冠；饰章；顶部 v.到达顶部；到达最高点', '1. A surfboard fin sliced the crest of a wave. 冲浪板尾部划破浪尖。 2. The hissing crest of the huge wave bites at your shoulder. 发出啸声的巨浪的浪峰劈头盖脑地向你袭来。 3. The rooster bristled his crest. 公鸡竖起了鸡冠。 4. The redness of her crest makes maples loss color. 她顶冠的艳红让枫叶失去了颜色。 5. As we crested the hill, we saw the castle. 我们登上了山顶,看见了城堡。', '过去式: crested 过去分词: crested 现在分词: cresting 第三人称单数: crests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sympathy', '[\'sɪmpəθi]', 'n.同情；同情心；同感；赞同；慰问', '1. I felt much sympathy for the blind. 我对盲人深感同情。 2. I have great sympathy for people in affliction. 我对那些受苦受难的人们充满同情。 3. The story stirred her sympathy. 这故事激起了她的同情心。 4. You shouldn\'t trade on her sympathy. 你不应该利用她的同情心。', '名词复数: sympathies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outrageously', '[aʊt\'reɪdʒəsli]', 'adv.残暴地；蛮横地', '1. Leila kept smiling her outrageously cute smile. 莱拉脸上始终挂着非常可爱的笑容。 2. These TV dinners are outrageously priced. 这些冷冻快餐贵得令人发指。 3. He flirts outrageously with his female clients. 他无耻地与女顾客调情。 4. A bigoted person;an outrageously bigoted viewpoint. 一个偏执的人；一个异常偏执的观点', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unconsolidated', '[ˌʌnkən\'sɒlɪˌdeɪtɪd]', 'adj.松散的(未固结的)；疏松的；非层状的', '1. Gravel is an unconsolidated mixture of rock fragments or pebbles. 砂砾是砾石岩石碎片或卵石的松散的混合物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chronical', '[\'krɒnɪkəl]', 'adj.长期的；慢性的', '1. Chronical prejudice will mislead you in making judgment on this event. 长期的成见会误导你对这件事情做判断。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fine', '[faɪn]', 'adj.好的；优质的；精致的；晴朗的；健康的；细微的 adv.合适地；恰好地 n.罚款；罚金；结尾 v.罚款；优化；净化；细化', '1. She is a fine singer, as her mother used to. 像她妈妈过去一样,她是个很好的歌手。 2. She has a remarkably fine voice. 她嗓音非常好。 3. We\'re going to a famous restaurant famous for its fine cuisine. 我们要去一家有名的餐馆,它是以精致的菜肴闻名。 4. Yesterday\'s forecast reported it\'d be fine. 不过,昨天的预报说是会放晴的。 5. That suits me fine. 这对我很合适。 6. The judge imposed a fine of ten pounds on him. 这个法官让他缴纳10英镑的罚款。 7. He was fined 200 dollars. 他被罚款200美元。', '形容词: finable 比较级: finer 最高级: finest 名词: fineness 过去式: fined 过去分词: fined 现在分词: fining 第三人称单数: fines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equilibrium', '[ˌiːkwɪ\'lɪbriəm]', 'n.平衡；均衡；平静', '1. He lost his equilibrium and fell into the lake. 他失去平衡，跌进湖里。 2. We have achieved an equilibrium in the economy. 我们已在经济上达到平衡。 3. He can\'t maintain enough equilibrium to ride a bike. 他骑自行车不能保持平衡。 4. We must try to maintain the equilibrium of supply and demand. 我们必须努力保持供求均衡。', '名词复数: equilibriums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('furnish', '[\'fɜːrnɪʃ]', 'vt.布置；装备；提供', '1. They are renting a furnished flat. 他们租用了一套带有家具的公寓房子。 2. We propose to furnish our own house according to our own taste. 我们建议按自己的爱好布置自己的房子。 3. They scouted around for some antiques to furnish their new apartment. 他们到处搜罗一些古董来装饰新居。 4. I am bound to furnish my antagonists with arguments, but not with comprehension. 我一定要向对手提供争论点，但并无予以理解的必要。', '名词: furnisher 过去式: furnished 过去分词: furnished 现在分词: furnishing 第三人称单数: furnishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bulky', '[\'bʌlki]', 'adj.庞大的；笨重的；肥大的', '1. Hollowcore concrete is bulky and comes from only a few regional sites. 中空混凝土是庞大的并且只来自一些地区场所。 2. Technicians pumped up their bulky white suits to make sure there were no leaks. 技师为他们庞大的白色衣服充满气体以确保衣服没有漏洞。 3. She dropped the bulky package twice. 她两次将那个笨重的包裹掉落下来。 4. The original sight was bulky and prone to mechanical issues, he said. 原来的视线是笨重的，很容易受机械的问题，他说。', '副词: bulkily 比较级: bulkier 最高级: bulkiest 名词: bulkiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rejuvenate', '[rɪ\'dʒuːvəneɪt]', 'v. 使 ... 年轻； 使 ... 恢复精神； 变年轻', '1. The mountain air will rejuvenate you. 山上的空气将使你变得年轻。 2. Only barbarians are able to rejuvenate a world in the throes of collapsing civilization. 的确，只有野蛮人才能使一个在垂死的文明中挣扎的世界年轻起来。', '名词: rejuvenation 过去式: rejuvenated 过去分词: rejuvenated 现在分词: rejuvenating 第三人称单数: rejuvenates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bliss', '[blɪs]', 'n.幸福；极乐；天赐的福', '1. They were in a state of bliss during the honeymoon. 他们在蜜月期间幸福无比。 2. The first six months of marriage were sheer bliss. 刚结婚的半年,他们沉浸在极乐之中。 3. Tom was swimming in bliss. 汤姆处于极乐之中。 4. Innocence is bliss. 无知便是福。', '形容词: blissful 副词: blissfully 名词: blissfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('locomotive', '[ˌloʊkə\'moʊtɪv]', 'n.火车头；机车 adj.运动的；火车头的；旅行的', '1. He is a locomotive engineer. 他是一名火车司机。 2. They detached the locomotive from the train. 他们使火车头与列车脱离了。 3. The locomotive was dashed to pieces. 机车撞得粉碎。 4. The locomotive pulled a long line of freight cars. 那台机车拖了一长列货车。 5. Hands and feet are locomotive organs. 手和脚是运动器官。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('technique', '[tek\'niːk]', 'n.技术；技巧；技能', '1. The technique is still at the experimental stage. 这项技术正处于实验阶段。 2. The workers are trying to apply modern techniques to this traditional craft. 工人们试图将现代技术用于这项传统工业。 3. In many sports physical fitness is not as important as technique. 在许多体育运动中，体能没有技巧重要。 4. Could you project a new marketing technique for us? 你能否为我们策划一个新的市场营销技巧?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('storage', '[\'stɔːrɪdʒ]', 'n.保管；贮藏；仓库；保管费；[计]存储器', '1. The best place for storage of money is a bank. 银行是存钱最好的地方。 2. The cave can be used for storage. 洞穴可以用来贮藏东西。 3. You should place the goods in storage. 你应该把货物贮藏起来 4. His furniture is in storage while he finds a new house. 他在找新房子时把家具存放在仓库里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('livestock', '[\'laɪvstɑːk]', 'n.家畜；牲畜', '1. He is good at breeding livestock. 他擅长畜养家畜。 2. There were cows, pigs and other livestock there. 那儿也有牛、猪和其他家畜。 3. They cramped the livestock in the ancient barns. 他们把牲畜关在老谷仓里。 4. Britain takes the lead in exporting livestock: cattle, sheep, pigs and horses. 英国在出口牛、羊、猪和马等牲畜上居领先地位。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('activity', '[æk\'tɪvəti]', 'n.活动；活跃 vt.表演 adj.厉害', '1. We love outdoor activity. 我们热爱户外活动。 2. We plan to expand our business activities in East Africa. 我们打算在东非扩展我们的商业活动。 3. The volcano is in activity. 这火山正活跃著。 4. There was a sudden spurt of activity in the housing market. 房产市场突然活跃了一阵子。 5. Busking is a fun activity for the performer. 街头表演对于街头艺人来说是一项有乐趣的活动。', '名词复数: activities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fresco', '[\'freskoʊ]', 'n.壁画', '1. This is a masterpiece in fresco. 这是一幅壁画法的杰作。 2. The frescos in the Sistine Chapel are world-famous. 西斯廷教堂的壁画举世闻名。', '名词: frescoer 名词复数: frescoes 过去式: frescoed 过去分词: frescoed 现在分词: frescoing 第三人称单数: frescoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('justify', '[\'dʒʌstɪfaɪ]', 'vt.替 ... 辩护；证明 ... 正当；调整版面', '1. He had to justify himself for his conduct. 他不得不为自己的行为辩白。 2. Don\'t try to justify your mistakes. 不要为自己的缺点辩护。 3. Nothing can justify your cheating on an exam. 任何事情都不能成为你考试作弊的理由。 4. Such action can be justified on the grounds of greater efficiency. 以提高功效为依据可以证明采取这种措施是正确的。', '过去式: justified 过去分词: justified 现在分词: justifying 第三人称单数: justifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grumpy', '[\'ɡrʌmpi]', 'adj.性情乖戾的；脾气暴躁的', '1. China has been a grumpy taker in this process. 在这过程中中国是个暴躁的攫取者。 2. If you find that your grumpy mood is becoming a habit, try expressive writing. 如果你觉得暴躁的情绪将成为一种习惯时，那么就试试写作吧。', '副词: grumpily 比较级: grumpier 最高级: grumpiest 名词: grumpiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('membrane', '[\'membreɪn]', 'n.【C】薄膜；膜状物', '1. A plastic membrane serves as selective diffusion barrier. 一层塑料薄膜起着选择性渗透屏障的作用。 2. A vibrating membrane in the ear helps to convey sounds to the brain. 耳膜的振动帮助声音传送到大脑。 3. Such membrane lipids are amphiphatic molecules. 这种膜的类脂是一种有两种亲和性的分子。', '形容词: membranal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drizzle', '[\'drɪzl]', 'vi.下毛毛雨 vt.细雨般地洒下 n.细雨', '1. It had been drizzling all day. 下了一整天的毛毛雨。 2. It\'s going to snow drizzle tomorrow. 明天要下毛毛雨。 3. Drizzle the lemon juice over the fish. 在鱼上洒点柠檬汁。 4. The dew on the branches drizzled our hair and shoulders. 枝头上的露珠润湿了我们的头发和双肩。 5. Would you like to go for a walk in the drizzle? 想去毛毛雨里散会儿步吗？', '形容词: drizzly 过去式: drizzled 过去分词: drizzled 现在分词: drizzling 第三人称单数: drizzles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inflexible', '[ɪn\'fleksəbl]', 'adj.不可弯曲的；僵硬的；顽固的；不可改变的；不容变更的', '1. The new plastic is completely inflexible . 这种新塑料是完全不可弯曲的。 2. As we grow old, joints become inflexible and hard to bend. 随着年龄的增长，关节变得僵硬，不易弯曲。 3. Something of awe now stole over me, as I gazed upon this inflexible iron animal. 我凝视着这只顽固的铁兽，不觉有点肃然起敬了。 4. Typically, our conscious mind is stubborn, inflexible and hard headed. 通常我们的有意识的心智是顽固不化的。', '副词: inflexibly 名词: inflexibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('volunteer', '[ˌvɑːlən\'tɪr]', 'n.志愿者；(自行生长的)植物 v.(自愿)做', '1. He enlisted as a volunteer in the army. 他以志愿兵从军。 2. He works as a volunteer at off time. 在业余时间 3. He volunteered a statement to the police. 他自动向警方供出情况。 4. Many people volunteer to work on the farms. 许多人自动到农场劳动。', '过去式: volunteered 过去分词: volunteered 现在分词: volunteering 第三人称单数: volunteers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impel', '[ɪm\'pel]', 'v.驱使；激励', '1. The President\'s speech impelled the nation to greater efforts. 总统的讲话激励国民更加努力。 2. Impelled by feelings of guilt, John wrote to apologize. 约翰有感愧疚，於是写信道歉。 3. I felt impelled to investigate the matter further. 我觉得自己有责任对事情作进一步调查。 4. I was so annoyed that I felt impelled to write a letter to the paper. 我非常恼怒，以致觉得非给报社写封信不可。', '过去式: impelled 过去分词: impelled 现在分词: impelling 第三人称单数: impels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proof', '[pruːf]', 'n.证明；证据；校样 adj.防 ... 的；耐 ... 的 vt.检验；给 ... 做防护措施', '1. This fact is too evident to require proof. 这事实很明显, 用不着证明。 2. Have you got any proof that you own this bike? 你有什么证据证明这辆自行车是你的？ 3. There are a few misprints which I will correct in proof. 有几处印错了,我将在校样上一一改正。 4. The shelter was proof against the bitter weather. 这个棚子可以避寒。 5. It is part of your duty to proof twenty pages. 校对20页是你分内之事。', '名词: proofer 过去式: proofed 过去分词: proofed 现在分词: proofing 第三人称单数: proofs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interfere', '[ˌɪntər\'fɪr]', 'vi.干涉；妨碍', '1. Don\'t interfere with my business. 不要干涉我的事情。 2. Constant interruptions interfere with my work. 一次又一次的干扰妨碍我的工作。 3. Don\'t allow pleasure to interfere with duty. 不要让娱乐妨碍了职责。', '副词: interferingly 名词: interferer 过去式: interfered 过去分词: interfered 现在分词: interfering 第三人称单数: interferes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('persistent', '[pər\'sɪstənt]', 'adj.坚持的；连续的；固执的', '1. He is a persistent pursuer of truth. 他是个坚持不懈追求真理的人。 2. His great success cannot depart from his persistent effort. 他取得这么大的成功和他坚持不懈的努力分不开。 3. A persistent cough may be a symptom of tuberculosis. 持续的咳嗽可能是肺病的症候。 4. His persistent questions finally goaded me into an angry reply. 他三番五次地问问题惹得我回答时也没有好气。', '副词: persistently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fitting', '[\'fɪtɪŋ]', 'adj.合适的；恰当的 n.试穿；配件；装配 动词fit的现在分词和动名词形式.', '1. A fitting end to the meal would be a glass of port. 餐后一杯波尔图葡萄酒是挺合适的。 2. It was, in fine, a fitting end to the story. 总之，这是故事很恰当的结尾。 3. He expressed his thoughts in clear and fitting language. 他用明白恰当的语言来表达他的思想。 4. The fitting-room is at the corner. 试衣间在拐角处。', '副词: fittingly 名词: fittingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discord', '[\'dɪskɔːrd]', 'n.不调和；不一致；[音]不谐和 vi.不一致；不协调', '1. What has brought discord into the family? 什么事使得这个家庭不和？ 2. He\'s been a source of discord and worry. 他成为不和和烦恼的根源。 3. Various discords have arisen over this question. 人们在这个问题上发生了不少争执。 4. The discord of his music was hard on the ear. 他演奏的不和谐音很刺耳。 5. The speaker\'s opinion discords with the principles of this society. 演讲者的意见与本会的原则不符。', '过去式: discorded 过去分词: discorded 现在分词: discording 第三人称单数: discords');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inspire', '[ɪn\'spaɪər]', 'vt.鼓舞；激发；产生；赋予...灵感 vi.吸入', '1. We\'re trying to inspire him with confidence. 我们在努力鼓舞他的自信心。 2. The sight inspired him with nostalgia. 这景象激起了他的怀旧之情。 3. The failure inspired him to greater efforts. 失败激发他作更大的努力。 4. You inspire me with admiration. 你使我产生爱慕之心。', '名词: inspirer 过去式: inspired 过去分词: inspired 现在分词: inspiring 第三人称单数: inspires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('progressive', '[prə\'ɡresɪv]', 'adj.先进的；前进的；渐进的；革新的(音乐上的） n.进步分子；革新主义者', '1. She is the most progressive writer of that times. 她是那个时代最进步的作家。 2. That famous progressive thinker was asked to deliver a speech at the meeting. 那位著名的进步思想家被邀请在会议上发表演讲。 3. History can not hold progressive movement. 历史无法阻挡前进的步伐。 4. He noted a progressive speech impediment. 他发觉，说话障碍逐渐厉害起来。 5. The butchers at Pingkiang killed progressive people. 平江惨案的那些刽子手，他们把进步分子杀了。', '副词: progressively 名词: progressiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('succinct', '[sək\'sɪŋkt]', 'adj.简洁的', '1. Milton summarizes the people\'s case in many such succinct passages. 弥尔顿在许多简洁的段落中概括了人民的处境。', '副词: succinctly 比较级: succincter 最高级: succinctest 名词: succinctness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grant', '[ɡrænt]', 'v.授予；同意；承认；认为 n.授予物；补助金；同意；给予；财产转让 Grant. n.格兰特(男名)', '1. Visa exemption does not grant the right to work. 豁免签证并不授予工作的权利。 2. We grant the truth of what you said. 我们同意你说的是事实。 3. I grant that your explanation is reasonable. 我承认你的解释是合理的。 4. I take it for granted you have read this book. 我认为你一定读过这本书。', '形容词: grantable 名词: granter 过去式: granted 过去分词: granted 现在分词: granting 第三人称单数: grants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discreet', '[dɪ\'skriːt]', 'adj.谨慎的；不引人注意的；朴素的，简易的', '1. It was not discreet of you to say that. 你那样说有欠考虑。 2. Be more discreet or you\'ll get yourself talked about. 要更谨慎些－－否则你就会成为人们的话柄。 3. I\'ll certainly be most discreet in my conversation. 我在谈话中当然会十分小心的。 4. It was a discreet apartment in a quiet street. 那是间位於一条僻静的街上不引人注意的公寓房间。', '副词: discreetly 名词: discreetness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('donate', '[\'doʊneɪt]', 'v.捐赠；捐献', '1. I can donate one hundred dollars at best. 我充其量只能捐助100美元。 2. We donate to the school endowment fund every year. 我们每年向学校的捐赠基金捐款。 3. The government calls on the youth to donate their blood voluntarily. 政府号召青年义务献血。', '名词: donator 过去式: donated 过去分词: donated 现在分词: donating 第三人称单数: donates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('protract', '[proʊ\'trækt]', 'vt.延长；托长；伸出', '1. To protract the suspense, he paused for a considerable period of time before telling us the result of the experiment. 为了延长悬念，他在告诉我们实验结果之前停顿了相当一段时间。', '形容词: protractive 副词: protractedly 名词: protractedness 过去式: protracted 过去分词: protracted 现在分词: protracting 第三人称单数: protracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sparse', '[spɑːrs]', 'adj.稀少的；稀疏的', '1. This is a country of sparse population. 这是个人口稀少的小国。 2. Species that were once sparse started to carpet the plots. 曾经稀少的物种开始遍布草原。 3. His pink scalp gleamed through his sparse hair. 他发红的头皮在稀疏的头发下泛微光。 4. The sparse vegetation will only feed a small population of animals. 稀疏的植物只能喂少量的动物族群。', '副词: sparsely 比较级: sparser 最高级: sparsest 名词: sparseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sanitation', '[ˌsænɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.公共卫生；卫生设备；下水道设施', '1. Sanitation is necessary to prevent this. 要防止病从口人就必需讲究卫生。 2. The people lived in that city can keep sanitation clean. 住在那个城市的人们能保持公共卫生的清洁。 3. They live in conditions of appalling sanitation. 他们在十分恶劣的卫生条件下生活。 4. Studies show that the disease has been cut by 77 percent in some areas through providing better water and sanitation. 研究表明，通过提供更好的水和卫生设备，有些地区的发病率减少了77%25。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exemplify', '[ɪɡ\'zemplɪfaɪ]', 'vt.例证；示范', '1. I will exemplify my point with a story. 我会用一个故事举例说明我的观点。 2. To exemplify this theory,let us examine some species of insect. 为举例说明这种理论，我们来检查一些种类的昆虫。 3. The plays of Wilds exemplify the comedy of manners. 王尔德的戏剧是风尚喜剧的典范。 4. The recent oil price rises exemplify the difficulties which the motor industry is now facing. 最近的石油涨价是汽车工业正面临的困难的一个例子。', '形容词: exemplifiable 名词: exemplifier 过去式: exemplified 过去分词: exemplified 现在分词: exemplifying 第三人称单数: exemplifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('authorize', '[\'ɔːθəraɪz]', 'vt.批准；委托；授权', '1. The committee authorized the payment of the money. 委员会批准该款之支付。 2. I\'ve been authorized by the court to repossess this property. 我得到法庭认可重新拥有这笔财产。 3. I have authorized him to act for me while I am away. 我已经委托他当我不在的时候代我处理。 4. He confidentially authorized me to act for him while he was abroad. 他信任地委托我在他出国期间代行他的职务。', '名词: authorizer 过去式: authorized 过去分词: authorized 现在分词: authorizing 第三人称单数: authorizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('colossal', '[kə\'lɑːsl]', 'adj. 巨大的； <口>异常的', '1. This is indeed a colossal success. 这确实是个巨大的成功。 2. But to go back to the old ways would be a colossal mistake. 但是，回到老路上将是一个巨大的错误。', '副词: colossally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consumption', '[kən\'sʌmpʃn]', 'n.消费；消耗；肺痨', '1. The government encourages individual consumption. 政府鼓励个人消费。 2. Internet shopping is a new way of consumption. 网上购物是当今消费的一种新途径。 3. The meat was condemned as unfit for human consumption. 这种肉已宣布不适宜人们食用。 4. The car scored well in fuel consumption. 那部汽车在燃料消耗方面获得好评。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shortage', '[\'ʃɔːrtɪdʒ]', 'n.不足；缺少，短缺', '1. The war was lost because of a shortage of munitions. 战争因军火不足而失败。 2. Power shortage browned out the city that winter. 那年冬天，由于电力不足，市里采取了部分停电供应措施。 3. He always bemoans the shortage of funds for research. 他总是叹息研究经费不足。 4. Continuance of the war will mean shortage of the food. 战争的持续意味着食品短缺。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indigestion', '[ˌɪndɪ\'dʒestʃən]', 'n.消化不良；不能理解', '1. I overate at the party last night and got violent indigestion. 昨日晚宴我吃多了，严重消化不良。 2. Her indigestion hindered her in her study. 她的领悟力差,因而影响她的学习。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subsidy', '[\'sʌbsədi]', 'n.津贴；补助金', '1. It\'s the old and the poor who suffer worst when subsidies are cut. 补助津贴一削减，最吃苦头的就是那些老人和贫民。 2. She qualifies for the unemployment subsidy . 她有权获得失业补贴。 3. The townsfolk can\'t understand why the Royal Shakespeare Company needs a subsidy. 市民不明白王室莎士比亚公司为什么需要一个补助金。', '名词复数: subsidies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barely', '[\'berli]', 'adv.几乎不；刚刚；勉强；少量地', '1. He is so weak that he can barely stand up. 他身体虚弱几乎站不起来。 2. I had barely started speaking when he interrupted me. 我刚刚开始讲话，他便打断了我。 3. We had barely enough money to last through the weekend. 我们的钱只能勉强维持到周末。 4. The room was barely furnished. 这个房间里陈设简陋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quilt', '[kwɪlt]', 'n.被状物；被子 v.缝被；缝制；用垫料填塞', '1. He bought a heavy quilt for the winter. 他买了一床厚被子过冬。 2. He wake to find that his quilt have slip off the bed. 他醒来发现被子从床上滑下来了。 3. If you air your quilt on such a wet day, it\'ll soak up the moisture. 如果在这么潮湿的天晒被子，被子就会把湿气都吸去。', '名词: quilter 过去式: quilted 过去分词: quilted 现在分词: quilting 第三人称单数: quilts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mend', '[mend]', 'vt.修理；修补；改进 vi.改过自新；改进；痊愈 n.修补；改进；修补处', '1. We need an electrician to mend the iron. 我们要请电工修理熨斗。 2. It won\'t take long to mend the car. 修理这辆汽车用不了很长时间。 3. He sent for someone to mend the broken window. 他叫人来修补破窗子。 4. You\'ll have to mend your ways if you want to be successful in your job. 如果你想在你的工作中取得成绩的话，你一定要有所改进。 5. It is never too late to mend. 改过不嫌晚。 6. The mends were almost invisible. 修补过的地方几乎看不出来。', '形容词: mendable 名词: mender 过去式: mended 过去分词: mended 现在分词: mending 第三人称单数: mends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bear', '[ber]', 'n.熊 v.忍受；负荷；结果；证实；生子女', '1. The hunter slashed at the bear with his knife. 猎人挥刀向熊猛烈砍去。 2. The bear has lived up to his reputation for stupidity. 这只熊果然名不虚传，笨得出奇。 3. I can\'t bear young people casting away their youth. 我无法忍受年轻人虚掷青春。 4. Girls whom can get easily may be hard to bear. 容易追求的女子,也许很难忍受。', '过去式: bore 过去分词: borne/born 现在分词: bearing 第三人称单数: bears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('absolve', '[əb\'zɑːlv]', 'vt.宣告...无罪；赦免', '1. The police absolved the suspect. 警方释放了嫌疑犯。 2. He cannot entirely absolve himself of the charge. 他不能完全开脱掉这一指责。 3. I absolve you from your vows. 我解除你的誓约。 4. The captain is absolved from all blame and responsibility for the shipwreck. 那位船长被免除了因船只失事而遭致的非难和罪责。', '形容词: absolvable 名词: absolver 过去式: absolved 过去分词: absolved 现在分词: absolving 第三人称单数: absolves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meticulous', '[mə\'tɪkjələs]', 'adj.一丝不苟的；缜密的', '1. He is noted for his meticulous scholarship. 他以治学严谨著称。 2. She is meticulous in her presentation of facts. 她介绍事实十分详细。 3. Their rooms had been prepared with meticulous care. 他们的房间是经过精心布置的。 4. The arrangements were meticulous. 布置得很缜密。', '副词: meticulously 名词: meticulosity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legislate', '[\'ledʒɪsleɪt]', 'v.制定法律；用立法规定', '1. It is the job of Parliament to legislate. 立法是议会的工作。 2. They promised to legislate to protect people\'s right to privacy. 他们承诺立法保护公民的隐私权。', '过去式: legislated 过去分词: legislated 现在分词: legislating 第三人称单数: legislates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lava', '[\'lɑːvə]', 'n.熔岩；火山岩', '1. The molten lava ran down the mountain. 熔岩从山上流下来。 2. That volcano cast forth lots of lava and ashes. 那火山喷了出大量熔岩和灰烬。 3. Lava could account for the mare infill on the Moon. 火山岩能解释月球表面大片的阴暗区的形成。 4. Back in the smelting, pull the lever to open the lava pit. 回到熔炼房间，拉下控制杆打开火山岩坑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('demolish', '[dɪ\'mɑːlɪʃ]', 'v.拆毁；破坏；驳倒；<口>吃光', '1. They have demolished the slum district. 贫民区已被拆除。 2. They\'re going to demolish that old building. 他们将拆毁那座旧建筑物。 3. It was an experience that completely demolished her confidence. 这个经历彻底摧毁了她的信心。 4. Her article brilliantly demolishes his argument. 她的文章精辟地批驳了他的论点。', '过去式: demolished 过去分词: demolished 现在分词: demolishing 第三人称单数: demolishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tendon', '[\'tendən]', 'n.腱', '1. A tendon consists of parallel fibres. 腱由平行的纤维组成。 2. The tendon had been so skillfully grafted in that the boy was able to flex his finger quite normally after four weeks. 腱的接合手术做得非常高明，那个男孩在四个星期之后，就能相当正常地伸屈他的手指了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('organism', '[\'ɔːrɡənɪzəm]', 'n.有机体；生物体；有机组织', '1. Germs may invade the organism. 细菌会侵入有机体。 2. Organism is the basic study of biology. 生物体是生物研究的基础领域。 3. The ameba is a very simple organism. 变形虫是很简单的生物体。 4. An organism adapts best when stresses are slightly increased. 当压力被稍微地提高时，是生物体适应的最好状况。', '形容词: organismal 副词: organismically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fellow', '[\'feloʊ]', 'n.家伙；同事；同伴；研究员；校董 adj.同伴的；同事的；同类的', '1. Jack is a clever fellow indeed. 杰克确实是个聪明的家伙。 2. I can\'t tolerate that rude fellow. 我不能容忍那个粗鲁的家伙。 3. That foolish fellow is looking for trouble. 那个愚蠢的家伙在自找麻烦。 4. He\'s a very nice fellow though bad-tempered. 他虽然脾气暴躁,但是一个很好的同事。 5. He recalled his fellow traveller with pleasure. 他愉快地回忆起他的旅伴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tendency', '[\'tendənsi]', 'n.趋势；倾向；秉性', '1. There is a tendency towards regional cooperation. 有一种地区性合作的趋势。 2. There is a growing tendency for people to work at home instead of in offices. 人们在家里而不是在办公室里工作的趋势日益增长。 3. Today there is a tendency for people to opt out of social activity. 现在,越来越多的人倾向于不参加社会活动。 4. They tried to stop the tendency of inflation. 他们设法阻止住了通货膨胀的势头。', '名词复数: tendencies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adherent', '[əd\'hɪrənt]', 'n.追随者；拥护者；信徒 adj.附着的；粘连的', '1. The movement is gaining more and more adherents. 这个运动得到了越来越多的追随者的支持。 2. He is a leader with many adherents. 他是个有众多追随者的领袖。 3. This is a kind of adherent substance. 这是一种粘性物质。', '副词: adherently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brain', '[breɪn]', 'n.脑；智力；智者；控制中心 vt.打 ... 的脑袋', '1. The drug may cause permanent brain damage. 这种药可能会引起永久性的脑部伤害。 2. His brain seems to be functioning normally. 他的大脑看起来功能正常。 3. His brain was clouded by vapours and dreams. 他的脑子里充满空想和梦幻。 4. She has a good brain. 她很有头脑。 5. I\'ll brain you if you don\'t keep quiet. 如果你不保持安静的话，我就敲你的脑袋。', '过去式: brained 过去分词: brained 现在分词: braining 第三人称单数: brains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('articulate', '[ɑːr\'tɪkjuleɪt]', 'adj.发音清晰的；善于表达的；有关节的 v.清楚地讲话；发音；以关节连接', '1. Articulate speech is essential for a teacher. 对教师来说,口齿清楚是必不可少的。 2. I\'m a little deaf, please articulate your words carefully. 我有些耳聋，请把话仔细地说清楚。 3. She\'s unusually articulate for a ten-year-old. 作为一个十岁的孩子来说，她的表达力是非常强的。 4. Young people are articulate about the skills they need for everyday life. 年轻人善于表达他们应付日常生活所需的技能。 5. She was too frightened to articulate. 她吓得连话也说不清。', '副词: articulately 名词: articulateness 过去式: articulated 过去分词: articulated 现在分词: articulating 第三人称单数: articulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fold', '[foʊld]', 'vt.包；折叠；交叉；拥抱 vi.翻倍；屈服；倒闭 n.折层；折痕', '1. Dark clouds folded the hills. 乌云笼罩着群山。 2. I folded the handkerchief and put it in my pocket. 我折好手绢，放进口袋里。 3. The paper should be folded in half. 这张纸应该对折。 4. The border guard folded his arms across his chest and glared the front. 边防战士双手交叉于胸前紧紧瞪着前方。 5. if a business folds, it closes because it is not able to make enough money. 如果有公司倒闭关门,那是因为它没办法赚取足够的钱。', '形容词: foldable 过去式: folded 过去分词: folded 现在分词: folding 第三人称单数: folds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glimpse', '[ɡlɪmps]', 'n.一瞥；一闪；略微；隐约感觉 v.瞥见', '1. He caught a glimpse of me when I passed by. 当我走过时，他瞥了我一眼。 2. A glimpse of her face will tell you that she is innocent. 你只要一看见她的脸就会明白，她是无辜的。 3. I only caught a glimpse of him sitting in the car, so I can\'t tell exactly what he looked like. 我只瞥见他坐在车里，所以我无法确切说出他长得什么样。 4. He caught a glimpse of her before she banished into the crowd. 他看见她一闪就在人群中消失了。 5. I glimpsed at her among the crowd before she disappeared from sight. 就在她即将消失在人群里之前，我瞥见了她。', '名词: glimpser 过去式: glimpsed 过去分词: glimpsed 现在分词: glimpsing 第三人称单数: glimpses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elementary', '[ˌelɪ\'mentri]', 'adj.基本的；初级的；元素的', '1. He is ignorant of even the most elementary facts. 他连最基本的事实都不知道。 2. They lack the most elementary sanitary facilities. 他们缺乏最基本的卫生设备。 3. This is the elementary rules of social conduct. 这是社会行为的基本原则。 4. This elementary school is affiliated to a university. 这所小学附属于一所大学。', '副词: elementarily 名词: elementariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tile', '[taɪl]', 'n.瓷砖；瓦片 v.盖瓦；铺瓷砖', '1. The reconciled reptiles rest on a fragile tile. 和解的爬行动物歇在易碎的瓷砖上。 2. We have put tiles on the wall behind the bath. 我们在浴缸后的墙上贴了瓷砖。 3. I entered the kitchen, with its old tile floor and its cherrywood cabinets. 我走进了厨房，年月久远的瓷砖地面，樱桃木材质的各色橱柜。 4. The rain came in for want of tile on the roof. 因房顶缺少瓦片，雨渗进来了。', '过去式: tiled 过去分词: tiled 现在分词: tiling 第三人称单数: tiles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unblemished', '[ʌn\'blemɪʃt]', 'adj.清白的；无疵的', '1. He had an unblemished reputation. 他的名声白璧无瑕。 2. This pure boy arrived fresh and unblemished. 这个纯真的男孩闯了进来，纯净无暇。 3. You essence is as pure and perfect as an unblemished jewel. 你的本质如同无瑕的珠宝一样完美无缺。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('primate', '[\'praɪmeɪt]', 'n.灵长目动物 n.(常大写)首席主教', '1. Compared to body size, the primate brain is larger than that of other animals. 相对身躯而言，灵长目动物的大脑比其他动物的大脑都要大些。 2. This is the rarest primate species on earth, and the Endangered Primate Rescue Center had only one couple in captivity. 这是世界上最罕见的灵长目物种，援救濒临灭绝灵长目动物中心只囚禁了一对。', '形容词: primatial');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('passive', '[\'pæsɪv]', 'adj.被动的；消极的 n.被动性', '1. He played a passive role in the marriage. 他在婚姻中扮演了一个被动的角色。 2. You are passive when you allow things to happen, but do nothing. 当你让这些事发生,而不做任何事来阻止它,你是消极的。 3. Good is the passive that obeys reason. 善是服从理智的被动性。 4. Passive tear suctioning force can be demonstrated by a Venturi tube model. 被动性泪液吸引之力量，可藉由文氏管模型来解释。', '副词: passively 名词: passiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('iceberg', '[\'aɪsbɜːrɡ]', 'n.冰山；冷若冰霜的人；（事物全貌的）一小部分；表面部分；显露部分；端倪初露的事物', '1. Most of the iceberg is under the water. 冰山的大部分在水面以下。 2. The ship was holed by an iceberg. 冰山把那船撞出了窟窿。 3. Four days after the Titanic set out, a very big iceberg floated towards her. 泰坦尼克号出发四天以后，一座巨大的冰山向它漂来。 4. He is an iceberg, very difficult to approach. 他是个冷淡而高傲的人,很难相处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fountain', '[\'faʊntn]', 'n.喷泉；源泉；储水容器；泉水 v.使像喷泉一样流', '1. She dabbled her fingers in the fountain. 她用手指在喷泉中玩水。 2. The parks of this city are famous for their ornate fountains. 这个城市的公园以其华丽的喷泉而著名。 3. Social life is the fountain of wisdom of writers. 社会生活是作家们智慧的源泉。 4. The brain is the ultimate fountain of ideas. 大脑是思想的根本源泉。', '过去式: fountained 过去分词: fountained 现在分词: fountaining 第三人称单数: fountains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obsolete', '[ˌɑːbsə\'liːt]', 'adj.已废弃的；过时的', '1. The army plans to phase out the equipment as it becomes obsolete. 军队计划淘汰这些设备，因为它们已经报废了。 2. This usage of the word is obsolete. 这个词的此类用法已经废弃了。 3. The obsolete regime is about to collapse. 那过时的政权即将崩溃。 4. You always depend on an obsolete viewpoint. 你老是信赖一个过时的观点。', '副词: obsoletely 名词: obsoleteness 过去式: obsoleted 过去分词: obsoleted 现在分词: obsoleting 第三人称单数: obsoletes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sinister', '[\'sɪnɪstər]', 'adj.邪恶的；不祥的；灾难性的；左边的', '1. He showed his sinister motive at last. 他终于露出了他那邪恶的用心。 2. The author\'s laconic prose manages to be both dexterous and sinister. 这位作者简洁的文字做到既洗练又有邪恶的暗示。 3. Maston was oppressed by sinister forebodings. 梅斯顿感到自己被一种不祥的预感紧紧地抓住了。 4. Events began to take on a more sinister aspect. 事情开始呈现较为不祥的征兆。', '副词: sinisterly 名词: sinisterness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deadline', '[\'dedlaɪn]', 'n.最后期限；(鉴于边上的)警戒线；截止时间', '1. I hope we can finish this before the deadline. 我希望我们能在最后期限之前完成这项工作。 2. She was working in haste to meet the deadline. 她匆忙工作是为了赶上最后期限。 3. We pulled out all the stops to meet the deadline. 我们竭尽全力在截止日期前完成了工作。', '过去式: deadlined 过去分词: deadlined 现在分词: deadlining 第三人称单数: deadlines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('racing', '[\'reɪsɪŋ]', 'n.竞赛；赛马 adj.竞赛用的；赛马用的 动词race的现在分词.', '1. Dog sled racing is the state sport of Alaska and is popular throughout North America and Europe. 狗拉雪橇竞赛是阿拉斯加州的州运动项目，并且在北美和欧洲都是非常流行的。 2. The horse racing is to be held at 3 p.m. tomorrow. 赛马比赛将于明天下午3点举行。 3. The cockpit of the driver\'s seat in a racing car is very small. 赛车的驾驶员座舱非常小。 4. Kentucky Derby is a racing classic. 肯塔基赛马大会是传统比赛。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exchange', '[ɪks\'tʃeɪndʒ]', 'v.交换；兑换 n.交换；交易所；兑换；交战', '1. May I exchange seats with you? 我和你调一个座位好吗? 2. You can exchange your car at our nearest office. 你可以到我们附近的公司换车。 3. We exchanged our opinions about the event at the meeting. 在会上，我们就此事交换了意见。 4. I\'d like to exchange some pounds for dollars. 我想把一些英镑兑换成美金。 5. He gave me an apple in exchange of an orange. 他给我一个苹果，交换一个橙子。', '形容词: exchangeable 过去式: exchanged 过去分词: exchanged 现在分词: exchanging 第三人称单数: exchanges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('waver', '[\'weɪvər]', 'v.动摇；摇曳；犹豫；颤抖 n.动摇；踌躇；挥动者；烫发器', '1. They did not waver in their support for him. 他们毫不动摇地支持他。 2. His courage never wavered. 他的勇气从未减弱。 3. The disaster caused him to waver in his faith. 这件灾难使他对信仰发生了动摇。 4. The flame wavered and then died. 火焰摇曳一下就熄灭了。 5. This caused them to waver in their faith. 这件事使他们的信仰动摇了。', '副词: waveringly 名词: waverer 过去式: wavered 过去分词: wavered 现在分词: wavering 第三人称单数: wavers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wither', '[\'wɪðər]', 'vi.枯萎，干枯；凋谢 vt.以鄙视等态度慑服某人；使枯萎，使凋谢，使衰弱', '1. The grapes withered on the vine. 葡萄藤上的葡萄都干瘪了。 2. Either of the flowers will wither soon without water. 任何一朵花没有水都会很快枯萎。 3. My days are like the evening shadow; I wither away like grass. 我的年日，如日影偏斜。我也如草枯干。 4. The early morning rose would wither on the branch if it could feel envy. 清晨的玫瑰如果知道妒忌，都会在枝头枯萎。', '过去式: withered 过去分词: withered 现在分词: withering 第三人称单数: withers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('profuse', '[prə\'fjuːs]', 'adj.很多的；丰富的；慷慨的；浪费的', '1. He made profuse apologies. 他再三道歉。 2. There are profuse blossoms. 那儿有很多花朵。 3. Many hybrids are profuse and persistent with flowers. 许多杂种开花繁茂耐久。 4. The truth is, that nature, seldom profuse, and seldom niggardly, has distributed her gifts more equally than she is generally supposed to have done. 事实是,自然总是将天赋公平地分配给人们,比人们通常认为的还要不偏不倚,很少过分地慷慨,也很少吝啬。', '副词: profusely 名词: profuseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circumspect', '[\'sɜːrkəmspekt]', 'adj.细心的；慎重的', '1. He was very circumspect in his financial affairs. 他对于自己的财务十分细心。 2. She is very circumspect when dealing with strangers. 她与陌生人打交道时十分谨慎。', '副词: circumspectly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('function', '[\'fʌŋkʃn]', 'n.职务；功能；函数；重大聚会；应变量，有相关关系者；取决于 vi.运行；起作用', '1. What is his function on the committee? 他在委员会里担任什么职务? 2. The teacher did not explain its grammatical function. 老师没有解释它的文法功能。 3. The function of the ear is to listen. 耳的功能是听。 4. Periodic change imposed on a controlled variable or a function by a controller. 通过控制器控制某一变量或函数进行周期性变化。 5. However, many system features and tasks will not function correctly. 但是,许多系统功能和任务将无法正常运行。', '形容词: functionless 过去式: functioned 过去分词: functioned 现在分词: functioning 第三人称单数: functions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('machinery', '[mə\'ʃiːnəri]', 'n.机械；(总称)机器', '1. We use tractors to pull farm machinery. 我们使用拖拉机牵引农业机械。 2. There was a ceaseless noise of machinery. 机器不停地发出噪音。 3. Some of the machinery is still standing idle. 有些机械仍然闲置着。 4. There was very little outlay on new machinery. 添置新机器的开支微乎其微。', '名词复数: machineries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('afflict', '[ə\'flɪkt]', 'vt.使苦恼；折磨', '1. I don\'t want to afflict you with my troubles. 我不想使你为我的困难而苦恼。 2. He was afflicted with cancer. 他患了癌症。 3. AIDS and cancer are maladies that afflict humanity. 爱滋病和癌症是折磨人类的疾病. 4. He will not afflict us beyond our power of endurance. 不会折磨得我们超过了承受能力的。', '形容词: afflictive 副词: afflictively 名词: afflicter 过去式: afflicted 过去分词: afflicted 现在分词: afflicting 第三人称单数: afflicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sulfur', '[\'sʌlfə]', 'n.【U】硫(磺) v.用硫磺处理', '1. Sulfur can be used to make gunpowder. 硫磺可以用来制造火药。 2. A sulfide compound contains at least two sulfur atoms per molecule. 多硫化物每个分子中至少含有两个硫原子的一种硫化物 3. Because the removal of phosphorus and sulfur require special condition that can be met only by the basic process. 因为除去钢中的磷和硫需要一些特殊的条件，这些条件只有碱性法才能满足。', '过去式: sulfured/sulphured 过去分词: sulfured/sulphured 现在分词: sulfuring/sulphuring 第三人称单数: sulfurs/sulphurs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fraction', '[\'frækʃn]', 'n.小部分；少许；分数；片段', '1. Mother\'s careful with her money, and spends only a fraction of her earnings. 母亲用钱很审慎,只花自己收入很小的一部分。 2. The door opened a fraction. 门稍微开了条缝。 3. I can only pay a fraction of my bill. 我只付我的帐单的一小部分。 4. Open the window a fraction, please. 请把窗户打开一点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extenuate', '[ɪk\'stenjʊˌeɪt]', 'vt. <古>减轻； 使人原谅； 使变瘦', '1. Because of extenuating circumstances, the court acquitted him of the crime. 因考虑到情有可原，法庭判他无罪。 2. Nothing can extenuate such appalling behavior. 这种骇人听闻的行径罪不可恕。', '形容词: extenuative 名词: extenuator 过去式: extenuated 过去分词: extenuated 现在分词: extenuating 第三人称单数: extenuates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slag', '[slæɡ]', 'n.熔渣；矿渣；<英俚> 荡妇 v.(英）严厉批评', '1. Some come off in the form of gases and others collect as slag. 有的化成气体跑掉了，有的结成了熔渣。 2. Some possibility exists to use the slag from the smeltery. 存在利用这家冶炼厂的矿渣的某种可能性。 3. Now he\'s left, she\'s always slagging off her old boss. 因原老板已走了，她就一个劲儿地褒贬他。', '形容词: slaggy 过去式: slagged 过去分词: slagged 现在分词: slagging 第三人称单数: slags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('balance', '[\'bæləns]', 'n.平衡；天平；平静；结余；差额；调和；制衡 vt.权衡；使平衡；抵消；称重量 vi.均衡；建立平衡', '1. The girl lost her balance and fell off the balance beam. 小女孩失去了平衡，从平衡木上摔了下来。 2. Great care must be taken in the use of the balance. 这种天平使用时必须十分当心。 3. He used a very sensitive torsion balance. 他利用了一架非常灵敏的扭力天平。 4. Sunday is a great time to balance out whatever area of your life has felt disordered as of late. 星期天是你最近动荡不安的生活得到平静的大好时机。 5. You have to balance the advantages of living in a big city against the disadvantages. 你必须权衡住在大城市的利与弊。 6. The dancer could balance on one toe. 舞蹈演员可以用一个脚趾平衡。', '过去式: balanced 过去分词: balanced 现在分词: balancing 第三人称单数: balances');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('admonish', '[əd\'mɑːnɪʃ]', 'vt.警告；训诫；告诫；提醒；敦促', '1. He was admonished for his carelessness. 他因粗心受到警告。 2. His wife admonished him not to drive too fast. 他的妻子警告他开车不要超速。 3. He has very sternly admonished student. 他十分严厉地训诫了学生。 4. He was admonished against doing wrong. 人们告诫他不要做坏事。', '副词: admonishingly 名词: admonisher 过去式: admonished 过去分词: admonished 现在分词: admonishing 第三人称单数: admonishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bleach', '[bliːtʃ]', 'n.漂白剂；漂白 v.变白；漂白', '1. I\'d like to buy a strong household bleach. 我想买强力家用漂白剂。 2. She scrubbed the counters down with bleach. 她用漂白剂把柜台擦洗干净。 3. I wonder if bleach will get that black spot out of my white jeans. 我在想漂白水能不能够将我白色牛仔裤上的班块清除。 4. How can the skin just bleach a bit ah? 皮肤怎么才能变白一点啊?', '过去式: bleached 过去分词: bleached 现在分词: bleaching 第三人称单数: bleaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('association', '[əˌsoʊʃi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.协会；社团；交往；联想；联合；结合', '1. Have you joined the teachers\' association? 你加入教师协会了吗? 2. About 20 people have registered in the association. 大约有20人已登记加入这一协会。 3. There is a hide-and-seek association with a leader who is nowhere to be found. 有一个躲猫猫社团，他们的团长现在还没有找到。 4. Horwath refers to Horwath International Association, a Swiss verein. 浩华是指浩华国际协会，为一个根据瑞士法律所组成的社团组织。', '形容词: associational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mammal', '[\'mæml]', 'n.哺乳动物', '1. The bat is the only mammal that can fly. 蝙蝠是唯一会飞的哺乳动物。 2. Is a meadow more complex than a mammal brain? 草地较之哺乳动物的大脑更复杂吗？', '形容词: mammalian');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('velocity', '[və\'lɑːsəti]', 'n.速度；迅速；速率', '1. The car was moving at such a velocity! 那辆汽车的速度简直太快了！ 2. The velocity of sound in water is more than four times that in air. 声音在水中的速度是在空气中的速度的4倍多。 3. Gazelles can move with astonishing velocity. 羚羊跑起来速度惊人。 4. The velocity of light is about 186,000 miles per second. 光速大约是每秒十八万六千英里。', '名词复数: velocities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deplore', '[dɪ\'plɔːr]', 'vt. 悲叹； 谴责； 对 ... 深感遗憾', '1. Aren\'t Republicans supposed to deplore the politics of victimhood? 难道不该谴责共和党借政治受害者来炒作的行径吗？ 2. Jefferson helped consolidate the power of the national government even as he claimed to deplore and reject such power. 即使杰斐逊公开谴责并抵制国家政府的权力，但他还是帮助巩固了这种权力。', '过去式: deplored 过去分词: deplored 现在分词: deploring 第三人称单数: deplores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incredulity', '[ˌɪnkrə\'djuːləti]', 'n.不轻信', '1. There was a hint of incredulity in her voice. 她的声音中流露出一丝迟疑。 2. \"You persist in your incredulity, Edmond,\" continued Faria. “你仍然不肯相信，爱德蒙，”法利亚继续说道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ancestor', '[\'ænsestər]', 'n.祖宗；祖先；原种', '1. During the festival the investor investigated his ancestor. 节日期间投资者调查了他的祖宗。 2. They said their ancestor was a famous hunter and a crack hunter. 他们说他们的祖宗是个有名的猎人，也是个神枪手。 3. People who share an ancestor are called relatives. 有同一个祖先的叫做亲戚。 4. She has worshipped her ancestor. 她已拜过她的祖先。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quarry', '[\'kwɔːri]', 'n.采石场；猎获物；来源；被追逐的目标 v.挖出；苦心找出', '1. This mountain was the site for a quarry. 这座山曾经有一个采石场。 2. The horseman aimed his lance at his quarry. 骑手把长矛对准了他的猎物。 3. Each sentence seems a quarry of rich meditations. 每一句话似乎都给人以许多冥思默想。 4. It took the police several days to track down their quarry. 警方用了几天时间追查到案中目标。 5. We watched the workmen quarry out a huge block of marble . 我们看到劳工们挖出一大块大理石。', '名词: quarrier 名词复数: quarries 过去式: quarried 过去分词: quarried 现在分词: quarrying 第三人称单数: quarries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('default', '[dɪ\'fɔːlt]', 'n.缺席；默认(值)；不履行责任 v.拖欠；默认；不履行义务；缺席', '1. The team lost a game by default. 那个队因没有出席而输掉比赛。 2. If not specified, the default value is no password. 如果未指定，则默认值为没有密码。 3. In 1997, no default of travel agent requiring payment of compensation occurred. 在一九九七年，并没有因旅行代理商不履行责任而需要支付赔偿。 4. He said he had to default on that loan. 他说他必须拖欠那笔债务。', '名词: defaulter 过去式: defaulted 过去分词: defaulted 现在分词: defaulting 第三人称单数: defaults');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('neutron', '[\'nuːtrɑːn]', 'n.中子', '1. Proton and neutron form a charge doublet. 质子和中子构成电荷双重态。 2. Neutron has no charge, either positive or negative. 中子不带电荷,既不带正电荷,也不带负电荷。 3. Let us calculate first how much energy is released when a free neutron decays. 让我们首先来计算一个自由中子的衰变会释放出多少能量。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('malevolent', '[mə\'levələnt]', 'adj.有恶意的；恶毒的', '1. Unfortunately there are some malevolent people out there and it is best not to take undue risks. 不幸的是在外面的世界里有一些恶毒的人，最好不要过分去冒险招惹他们。 2. As Father Ralph came in holding Meggie\'s hand, her malevolent gaze beat the child\'s down. 当拉尔夫神父拉着麦琪的手走进来时，她那恶毒的眼光马上压倒了孩子。', '副词: malevolently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('direct', '[də\'rekt]', 'adj.直接的；笔直的；坦白的 v.对准；指挥；指示；命令', '1. I\' m in direct contact with the hijackers. 我与劫机者保持着直接的联系. 2. Keep product away from direct sunlight and store in a dry cool place. 置放在不受阳光直射,干燥通风的地方。 3. He is very direct, so you always know what his real views are. 他为人很直率, 所以你总能知道他的真实想法。 4. The guide directed our attention to the other picture. 讲解员要我们注意另一幅画.', '过去式: directed 过去分词: directed 现在分词: directing 第三人称单数: directs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('miserly', '[\'maɪzərli]', 'adj.吝啬的；少量的', '1. He is miserly with both his time and his money. 他对于自己的时间和金钱都是吝啬的。 2. Their miserly offer is unlikely to be accepted. 他们极少的出价不大可能会被接受。', '名词: miserliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blanket', '[\'blæŋkɪt]', 'n.毛毯；覆盖物；排字版 vt.覆盖；用毯子裹；扑灭；挡风；使包含 adj.包含所有的；适用于所有情形的', '1. He threw a blanket over the injured man. 他急忙给受伤的人披上条毯子。 2. They cuddled up (together) under the blanket. 他们盖著毯子(在一起)搂著。 3. The nurse carried in a baby wrapped (up) in a warm blanket. 保母抱著个孩子进来，孩子身上裹著暖暖的毯子。 4. The ground was covered by a thick blanket of snow. 地面上覆盖着厚厚的一层雪。 5. The countryside was blanketed with snow/fog. 乡村被雪[雾]覆盖著。 6. A blanket insurance policy insures a car against all kinds of accidents. 一张综合保险单担保汽车一切意外事件。', '过去式: blanketed 过去分词: blanketed 现在分词: blanketing 第三人称单数: blankets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disrupt', '[dɪs\'rʌpt]', 'vt.干扰；打断；妨碍；使分裂；使破裂', '1. Protesters tried to disrupt the meeting. 抗议者试图扰乱会议。 2. The communication was disrupted by the storm. 暴风雨使交通中断。 3. The bad weather has seriously disrupted supplies of food. 恶劣的天气严重地妨碍了食品的供应。 4. The war seemed likely to disrupt the state. 战争可能使这个国家分裂。', '名词: disrupter 过去式: disrupted 过去分词: disrupted 现在分词: disrupting 第三人称单数: disrupts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rural', '[\'rʊrəl]', 'adj.农村的，乡村的，田园的', '1. The disease occurs most frequently in rural areas. 那疾病多见於农村地区。 2. Rural areas have been worst hit by the strike. 受罢工影响最严重的是乡村地区。 3. The rural scenery was so beautiful that he decided to stay one more week. 乡村风光太美了，以致于他决定再多呆一星期。 4. Nine tenths of the population in rural areas live from hand to mouth. 农村地区90%25的人仅够糊口。', '副词: rurally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('destined', '[\'destɪnd]', 'adj. 命中注定的； 去往 ... 的 destine的过去式和过去分词', '1. He is only beginning to realize the role he is destined to play in the great saga. 他刚开始认识到他在这伟大的冒险故事里所扮演的角色是命中注定的。 2. If all things have being destined, then is that mean sometimes the destiny depends on a particular time? 如果命运是命中注定的，是不是说某些时候命运是随某个特定时代而定的？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brew', '[bruː]', 'v.酿造；泡（茶）；酝酿；策划 n.酿造物；（酿造物的）质地；混合物', '1. He brews his own beer at home. 他在家自己酿造啤酒。 2. The tea is brewing and will be served soon. 茶正在泡，一会儿就送来。 3. A storm is brewing. 暴风雨正在酝酿中。 4. They are brewing a plot behind the scenes. 他们正在幕后策划一个阴谋。 5. The machine produces a brew that is dark in colour and complex in taste. 这台机器酿造出来的酒颜色很深，味道很复杂。', '名词: brewage 过去式: brewed 过去分词: brewed 现在分词: brewing 第三人称单数: brews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('senate', '[\'senət]', 'n.参议院；大学理事会', '1. The Senate confirms all treaties. 所有的条约都由参议院批准。 2. The Senate has voted to support the President\'s defense plans. 参议院已经投票支持总统的防卫计划。 3. The Senate resolved to accept the President\'s budget proposals. 参议院通过决议接受总统的预算建议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('furniture', '[\'fɜːrnɪtʃər]', 'n.家具；设备，装置；床罩；必要的附属品；【会计】家俬', '1. We will buy some furniture for our new house. 我们得给我们的新房子买些家具。 2. This old table is a valuable piece of furniture. 这张旧桌子是一件很珍贵的家具。 3. The antique furniture was made in 1700. 这件古老的家具是1700年制造的。 4. Children\'s furniture must withstand kicks and blows. 孩子用的家具必须经得起拳打脚踢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('variant', '[\'veriənt]', 'n.变体 adj.不同的', '1. Allophone is a phonetic variant of a phoneme. 音位变体就是音位的语音变异。 2. The story has many variants. 这个故事有很多说法。 3. One kind of elemental atoms and all other elemental atoms are variant. 一种元素的原子与所有其它元素的原子是不同的。 4. Working function is variant from request of boss. 工作职责与上司的要求不一致。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pinpoint', '[\'pɪnpɔɪnt]', 'v.精确地找到；瞄准；使突出 n.极小之物；精确位置 adj.精确的；微小的', '1. It\'s difficult to pinpoint the cause of the accident. 很难清楚地找到事故发生的原因。 2. With this device, we can pinpoint your exact location. 有了这个仪器，我们可以精确地标出你的位置。 3. We need to pinpoint our target market. 我们需要明确指出我们的市场目标。 4. We pinpointed the flaws in his argument. 我们突出他辩论中的错误。 5. There is only a pinpoint of light in the cave. 山洞中只能见到一丝光线。 6. They can control precisely where the nanotube penetrates a cell, for example, and een pinpoint smaller cell structures, such as the nucleus or mitochondrion. 例如他们能精确的控制纳米管插入细胞的位置，甚至能定位到更小的细胞结构如细胞核或线粒体。', '过去式: pinpointed 过去分词: pinpointed 现在分词: pinpointing 第三人称单数: pinpoints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('withdraw', '[wɪð\'drɔː]', 'vt.撤回；取回；撤退；提款 vi.撤退；退缩；走开', '1. In view of members reservation and request for further information, the Administration agreed to withdraw the item. 鉴于委员有所保留,并要求取得进一步资料,政府当局同意撤回该项目。 2. He wanted to withdraw his name from the guest list. 他想从客人名单中撤出自己的名字。 3. I\'d like to withdraw some money from my account. 我想从户头里提出一些钱。 4. The troops have been withdrawn from the danger area. 部队已经撤出危险地带。 5. Tell the men to withdraw from their new position. 告诉那些人从新的阵地上撤出。', '形容词: withdrawable 名词: withdrawer 过去式: withdrew 过去分词: withdrawn 现在分词: withdrawing 第三人称单数: withdraws');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('portray', '[pɔːr\'treɪ]', 'vt.描写；描绘；饰演', '1. It is difficult to portray feelings in words. 感情很难用言语来描写。 2. The book portrays the life of an actor. 这本书描述了一个演员的一生。 3. The picture portrays a beautiful sunset. 这幅画描绘了落日美景。 4. The actor is trying his best to portray the role of Hamlet. 这位演员尽力扮演哈姆雷特的角色。', '形容词: portrayable 名词: portrayer 过去式: portrayed 过去分词: portrayed 现在分词: portraying 第三人称单数: portrays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dedicate', '[\'dedɪkeɪt]', 'vt.致力于；献出；提献辞', '1. She dedicated her life to science. 她毕生致力于科学。 2. I will dedicate myself to science in the future. 我将来一定要投身于科学事业。 3. I dedicate this song to my wife. 我要把这首歌献给我太太。 4. I\'d like to dedicate the book to my parents. 我想把这本书献给我的父母。', '名词: dedicator 过去式: dedicated 过去分词: dedicated 现在分词: dedicating 第三人称单数: dedicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allure', '[ə\'lʊr]', 'v.诱惑；吸引 n.诱惑力；吸引力', '1. I wanted to allure my opponent to my place and attack him. 我想要把我的诱惑抛给对手然后把他吸引到我的地盘上然后攻击他。 2. Rewards allure men to brave danger. 重赏之下，必有勇夫。 3. In order to allure more customers,we\'ve stocked all types of cream. 为了吸引更多的顾客，我们进了各种面霜。 4. He can\'t resist the allure of the pretty waitress. 他无法抵抗漂亮的女招待的引诱。', '副词: alluringly 名词: allurement 过去式: allured 过去分词: allured 现在分词: alluring 第三人称单数: allures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entrap', '[ɪn\'træp]', 'v.诱捕；使陷入圈套', '1. The hunters used nets to entrap the lion. 猎人们以罗网诱捕狮子。 2. He felt he had been entrapped into marrying her. 他觉得和她结婚是上了当。 3. The enemy came upon us only to be entrapped and wiped out. 敌军发动袭击，结果反陷入我方伏击而被歼灭。', '名词: entrapment 过去式: entrapped 过去分词: entrapped 现在分词: entrapping 第三人称单数: entraps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oracle', '[\'ɔːrəkl]', 'n.神谕；神谕处；传达神谕的人；能提供可靠意见的人', '1. In times of difficulty, she prayed for an oracle to guide her. 在困难的时候,她祈祷神谕来指引她。 2. The earth is the great parent of all, the stones are her bones; these we may cast behind us; this, I think, the oracle means. 大地是万物之母，石头就是她的尸骨。我们可以往身后扔石头，我想神谕说的就是这个意思。 3. This oracle was still flourishing in 332 B.C. 这个神示殿在公元前332年依然很兴旺。 4. They consulted the oracle at Delphi. 他们在德尔斐神示所向神请示。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enrage', '[ɪn\'reɪdʒ]', 'vt.激怒；使暴怒', '1. Death Wish and Enrage effects no longer stack. 死愿和激怒的效果不叠加了。 2. He started another matter to enrage me, but I didn\'t care. 他又提出另一问题，想以此激怒我，可我并没在意。', '名词: enragement 过去式: enraged 过去分词: enraged 现在分词: enraging 第三人称单数: enrages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emphasize', '[\'emfəsaɪz]', 'vt.强调；着重；使突出', '1. He emphasized the importance of careful driving. 他强调小心驾驶的重要性。 2. We cannot emphasize too much the importance of learning English. 我们再怎样强调学英文的重要性也不为过。 3. Which word should I emphasize? 我应该重读哪个词? 4. I would like to emphasize that we are ready to meet the management at any time. 我想着重指出，我们愿意在任何时候与管理部门会谈。', '过去式: emphasized 过去分词: emphasized 现在分词: emphasizing 第三人称单数: emphasizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sever', '[\'sevər]', 'v.切断；脱离；分开', '1. She had to sever all ties with her parents. 她不得不断绝与父母的一切联系。 2. This action will sever the object\'s link to its master. 该操作将切断此对象与其主控文档的链接。 3. His arm was severed from his body in the accident. 在那次意外中，他的手臂被切断了。 4. We must never sever the cultural vein of our nation. 我们不能割断民族的文化血脉。', '过去式: severed 过去分词: severed 现在分词: severing 第三人称单数: severs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inactive', '[ɪn\'æktɪv]', 'adj.不活动的；停用的；怠惰的', '1. Some animals are inactive during the daytime. 有些动物白天不活动。 2. Hedgehogs are inactive in winter. 刺猬在冬天不活动。 3. It occurred to me that there were many inactive machines in the factory. 我忽然想起来工厂里有许多停用的机器。 4. Bears are inactive during the winter. 熊在冬天变得怠惰。', '副词: inactively 名词: inactivity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feverish', '[\'fiːvərɪʃ]', 'adj.发烧的；兴奋的', '1. The child is a bit feverish. 这孩子有点发烧。 2. The feverish boy soon infected other children. 发烧的男孩很快传染了其他孩子. 3. He said later, \"I was almost feverish with excitement. 他后来说：“我简直兴奋得发狂。 4. She was in a state of feverish agitation. 她在一种剧烈激动的状态中。', '副词: feverishly 名词: feverishness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aviation', '[ˌeɪvi\'eɪʃn]', 'n.航空；飞机制造业', '1. He devoted all his life to China\'s aviation. 他的一生都奉献给了中国的航空事业。 2. At that time aviation was still in its infancy. 当时航空仍在萌芽阶段。 3. Jets are a new development in aviation. 喷气式飞机是航空事业上的一个新成就。 4. In old China,there was hardly any machine- building industry,to say nothing of automobile and aviation industries. 旧中国几乎没有机器制造业，更不用说汽车制造业和飞机制造业了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pollute', '[pə\'luːt]', 'v.污染；弄脏', '1. Our store never sells books which pollute the mind. 我们书店从不出售污染心灵的书籍。 2. We should not pollute our rivers with waste. 我们不应让废弃物污染我们的河川。', '名词: polluter 过去式: polluted 过去分词: polluted 现在分词: polluting 第三人称单数: pollutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tide', '[taɪd]', 'n.趋势；潮流；潮汐；潮水 v.渡过；（使）随潮漂流', '1. For a moment the tide almost turned against him. 在短短的时间内，舆论的趋势几乎变得对他不利。 2. We should be naturalized to the new tide of the world. 我们必须顺应新的世界潮流。 3. It once again proves that no one can stem the tide of history. 这再一次地证明，历史的潮流是谁也阻挡不住的。 4. The attraction of the moon for the earth causes the tide. 月亮对地球的引力引起潮汐。 5. The loan is enough to tide them over the difficulties. 这笔贷款足以使他们渡过难关。', '过去式: tided 过去分词: tided 现在分词: tiding 第三人称单数: tides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glossary', '[\'ɡlɑːsəri]', 'n.词汇表；术语汇编', '1. There is a glossary at the end of the textbook. 这本教科书后面有词汇表。 2. The text is supplemented by an adequate glossary. 正文附有一个详细的词汇表。 3. He put a tick beside each word in the glossary that he had learned by heart. 他在词表中每一个已熟记的生词旁做了个记号。 4. There is a definition of infants in the glossary. 在术语表中有对婴幼儿的定义。', '形容词: glossarial 名词: glossarist 名词复数: glossaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contest', '[\'kɑːntest]', 'n.竞赛；比赛 vt.驳斥；争取 vi.奋斗', '1. She won a gold medal for her fine performance in the contest. 她在竞赛中成绩优异获金牌。 2. This football match is an unequal contest. 这场足球赛是一场实力悬殊的比赛。 3. Janet said she is thinking about attending a KTV contest. 珍妮说她正考虑参加一个KTV歌唱比赛。 4. I intend to contest the judge\'s decision in another court. 我准备下次开庭时反驳法官的判决。', '形容词: contestable 名词: contestation 过去式: contested 过去分词: contested 现在分词: contesting 第三人称单数: contests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fortune', '[\'fɔːrtʃən]', 'n.命运；财产；运气', '1. Everyone is the architect of his own fortune. 每个人都是自己命运的创造者。 2. An ill marriage is a spring of ill fortune. 不良的婚姻是恶运的来源。 3. He dreamed of making a fortune. 他梦想发大财。 4. I rate his fortune at$10,000. 我估计他有1万美元的财产。', '过去式: fortuned 过去分词: fortuned 现在分词: fortuning 第三人称单数: fortunes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('correlate', '[\'kɔːrəleɪt]', 'vt.使相互关联 vi.关联 n.相关物', '1. Research workers find it hard to correlate the two sets of figures. 研究人员发现很难使这两组数字互相关连。 2. We can often correlate age with frequency of illness. 年龄的大小往往与发病率有关。 3. The results of this experiment do not correlate with the results of earlier ones. 这次试验的结果与以往试验的结果毫不相干。 4. Hatred is a correlate of love. 恨与爱是互相关联的。', '过去式: correlated 过去分词: correlated 现在分词: correlating 第三人称单数: correlates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('develop', '[dɪ\'veləp]', 'v.发展；发育；开发；冲洗(照片)', '1. Modern music was first developed in Italy. 现代音乐最初是在意大利发展起来的。 2. China can\'t develop in isolation from the rest of the world. 中国的发展离不开世界。 3. Plants develop from seeds, but many animals developed from eggs. 植物由种子发育而成,而许多动物由卵子发育而来。 4. Investors agreed to pool their resources to develop the property. 投资者们同意把大家的资源放在一起共同使用,来开发这块地产。', '形容词: developable 过去式: developed 过去分词: developed 现在分词: developing 第三人称单数: develops');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seasoning', '[\'siːzənɪŋ]', 'n.调料', '1. This sauce uses mushroom as its seasoning. 这调味酱用蘑菇作调料。 2. The leaves of this plant can be used as a seasoning. 这种植物的叶子，可用作调料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dominate', '[\'dɑːmɪneɪt]', 'v.支配；控制；统治；占优势；俯视；高耸于', '1. That way, he can dominate the game. 那样他才能支配比赛。 2. He desires to dominate over others. 他很想支配别人。 3. He has authority, but he doesn\'t try to dominate (others). 他有权威 4. They had the ambition to dominate this small country. 他们有控制这个小国的野心。', '形容词: dominative 名词: dominator 过去式: dominated 过去分词: dominated 现在分词: dominating 第三人称单数: dominates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('essence', '[\'esns]', 'n.精髓；本质；要素；香精', '1. Flavor of life is always sweet, because they always taste the essence of life. 生活的味道总是甜蜜的,因为他们总是品尝到生活的精髓。 2. Simplicity is the essence of good taste. 纯朴是情趣高尚的主要因素。 3. Caution is the essence of that man\'s character. 谨慎是那人性格的本质。 4. The two things are the same in outward form but different in essence. 那两样东西在外表上相同，但在本质上不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stock', '[stɑːk]', 'n.存货；储备；树干；股票；股份；家畜；血统；汤汁；声望 v.采购；储存；供给；发新芽 adj.惯用的；存货的', '1. We have a large stock of tinned fruit. 我们有大批水果罐头的存货。 2. The grocer\'s has plenty varieties of goods in stock. 杂货商有种类繁多的存货。 3. We need to replenish our stocks of coal. 我们需要再次补充煤的储备。 4. Branches grow from the stock of the tree. 树枝是从树干上生长出来的。 5. We must stock up with food for the holiday. 我们必须采购一些食品以备假期之需。 6. She\'s tired of her husband\'s stock jokes. 她已听厌了丈夫那老一套的俏皮话。', '名词: stockage 过去式: stocked 过去分词: stocked 现在分词: stocking 第三人称单数: stocks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crystal', '[\'krɪstl]', 'n.水晶；结晶体；表蒙子 adj.透明的；晶体的', '1. I lost my crystal necklace at the party. 我在晚会上丢失了水晶项链。 2. This set of crystal wine cups is very expensive. 这套水晶玻璃酒杯非常昂贵。 3. This kind of crystal takes the shape of an irregular rhombus. 这种结晶体呈不规则菱形。 4. Can you fit me up with a new watch crystal? 你能给装一块新的表蒙玻璃吗? 5. The bird flew into the crystal clear window. 这只小鸟撞上了完全透明的窗户。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lodge', '[lɑːdʒ]', 'n.小屋；巢穴；门房；传达室；支部 v.存放；临时住宿；安顿；提出(报告、抗议等)', '1. We drove to our lodge on the lake for the summer. 我们驱车来到湖滨小屋度夏。 2. Yet the beaver lodge remained sturdy and strong. 然而，海狸的巢穴却依然强韧坚固。 3. He makes his house, or lodge, by piling a great mass of sticks and roots in a big cone on a solid foundation at the bottom of the pond and weighting them down with mud. 它在池塘底部一个地基坚固的大锥状穴中堆积大量的树枝和草根，用泥巴压实，建造起自己的家，或者说是巢穴。 4. They were immediately admitted into the lodge. 他们立刻被让进门房。 5. You can lodge the valuables in the bank. 你可以把贵重物品存放在银行里。', '过去式: lodged 过去分词: lodged 现在分词: lodging 第三人称单数: lodges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evaluate', '[ɪ\'væljueɪt]', 'vt.评价；评估', '1. Let\'s evaluate the evidence. 让我们评定一下此证据的价值。 2. The school has only been open for six months, so it\'s too early to evaluate its success. 这所学校开办还不过六个月，所以要对它的成绩作出评价为时尚早。 3. Enterprise should acquaint with its storage status, that\'s the reason why it needs to evaluate the storage material. 企业应对自身库存状况有清楚的了解,这就需要对各个物资做出评价。 4. At the conclusion of the test run, evaluate the test results. 在测试完成之后,对测试的结果进行评估;', '形容词: evaluative 名词: evaluation 过去式: evaluated 过去分词: evaluated 现在分词: evaluating 第三人称单数: evaluates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prize', '[praɪz]', 'n.奖品；奖金；奖赏 vt.珍视；估价 adj.奖品的；得奖的；一流的', '1. The boys competed with each other for the prize. 那些男孩子为赢得奖品而互相竞争。 2. First prize in the raffle is a holiday for two in Paris. 抽奖销售的头奖是两个人到巴黎度假旅游。 3. The champion team will win the cup and prize. 比赛的冠军将获得奖杯和奖金。 4. They all concurred in giving him the prize. 他们一致同意给他奖赏。 5. I still prize all those early pamphlets . 我仍珍视所有的那些早期小册子。 6. She will use the prize money to help pay for my education. 她要用这笔奖金支付部分学费。', '过去式: prized 过去分词: prized 现在分词: prizing 第三人称单数: prizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stand', '[stænd]', 'v.站立；忍受；位于；停滞 n.站立；货摊；停顿；看台', '1. I don\'t think the chair is firm enough to stand on. 我觉得这椅子不够稳固,不能站人。 2. I twisted my ankle, and I couldn\'t stand up. 我的脚踝扭伤,简直无法站起来。 3. She is funny, but I can\'t stand her. 她滑稽,但我无法忍受她。 4. Several pine trees stand erect on the hillside. 几棵青松挺立在山坡上。 5. He took his stand near the window. 他站在窗旁。', '名词: stander 过去式: stood 过去分词: stood 现在分词: standing 第三人称单数: stands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ecstasy', '[\'ekstəsi]', 'n.狂喜；入迷 Ecstasy. n.摇头丸', '1. Love brings ecstasy and relieves loneliness. 爱带来狂喜，减轻孤独。 2. Davidson\'s eyes shone with ecstasy. 戴维逊的双眼发出狂喜的光芒。 3. His ecstasy to the pop music is unbelievable. 他对流行音乐的入迷是令人难以置信的。 4. Tantra teaches that lovemaking between a man and woman, when entered into with awareness, is a gateway to both sexual and spiritual ecstasy. 坦陀罗教导男女之间的做爱，当进入知晓的时候，是性和精神入迷的道路。 5. The drug is commonly known as Ecstasy. 这种致幻药通常称作摇头丸。', '名词复数: ecstasies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('penchant', '[\'pentʃənt]', 'n.喜好(倾向)', '1. She has a penchant for Indian food. 她爱吃印度食物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('peck', '[pek]', 'v.啄；连续敲击；<口>轻吻 n.啄痕；啄食；<口>轻吻 n.配克；<口>大量', '1. That bird tried to peck me. 那只鸟想啄我。 2. The bird pecked at the bread crumbs. 鸟儿啄食面包屑。 3. She is pecking away at the keys of a typewriter. 她不停地敲打着打字机的键。 4. The boy started pecking at the keys of the piano. 男孩开始在钢琴上乱弹一气。 5. The parrot gave me a sharp peck on the finger. 鹦鹉把我的手指啄得很疼。', '过去式: pecked 过去分词: pecked 现在分词: pecking 第三人称单数: pecks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('untapped', '[ˌʌn\'tæpt]', 'adj.塞子未开的；未使用的', '1. An untapped cask of wine is stored quite well. 一桶未去塞的酒储存的很好。 2. Wind is an untapped energy resource. 风力是未使用的能源。 3. Kids have a natural sense of industry that goes largely untapped. 孩子们身上有一种在很大程度上未被开发的勤奋天赋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repudiate', '[rɪ\'pjuːdieɪt]', 'v.拒绝；拒付；断绝；否认', '1. The new government repudiated the treaty signed by the former government. 新政府拒绝履行前任政府签订的条约。 2. He repudiated the court\'s decision to offer bail. 他不接受法庭的保释裁决。 3. He would repudiate all debts incurred by his son. 他拒绝偿还他儿子的一切债务。 4. She repudiated her only daughter. 她与她的独生女儿断绝了母女关系。', '形容词: repudiative 名词: repudiator 过去式: repudiated 过去分词: repudiated 现在分词: repudiating 第三人称单数: repudiates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('long', '[lɔːŋ]', 'adj.长的；冗长的；久的；长音的 adv.长期地；久地；用于名词后强调某事发生在某整段时间 v.渴望 n.长时间；长音节；囤积商品者', '1. She was slender and had long dark hair. 她身材苗条，有一头长长的黑发。 2. She bought some roses with long stems. 她买了一些枝干很长的玫瑰花。 3. He delivered a long prose full of platitudes. 他发表了一篇充满陈词滥调的文章。 4. I haven\'t seen him for a long while. 我已经很久没见到他了。 5. I haven\'t known her long. 我认识她不久。 6. She longed to be back in China. 她渴望回到中国。 7. This won\'t take long. 这要不了多久。', '比较级: longer 最高级: longest 过去式: longed 过去分词: longed 现在分词: longing 第三人称单数: longs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agrarian', '[ə\'ɡreriən]', 'adj.土地的；耕地的 n.平均地权论者', '1. This was a feature of agrarian development in Britain. 这是大不列颠土地发展的一个特征。 2. In Lincoln\'s time the US was largely an agrarian society. 在林肯时代，美国大部分地区还是农业社会。 3. Since the agrarian reform polarization has taken place among the peasants 在土地改革后，农民发生了分化。', '副词: agrarianly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shake', '[ʃeɪk]', 'v.摇动；震动；握手 n.片刻；摇晃；<美口>奶昔', '1. Give the bottle a couple of shakes before pouring the juice. 倒果汁前，先把瓶子摇几下。 2. He shook his head in disapproval. 他摇了摇头表示反对。 3. His voice shook with fear. 他害怕得声音发抖。 4. It\'s time to shake out the red flag. 是把这面红旗打开的时候了。 5. He finished the bottle of wine in a shake. 他片刻功夫就把一瓶酒喝完了。', '形容词: shakable 过去式: shook 过去分词: shaken 现在分词: shaking 第三人称单数: shakes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('campaign', '[kæm\'peɪn]', 'n.运动；战役；活动；竞选运动 v.参加竞选；从事运动', '1. The campaign was a blockbuster. 这次竞选运动声势浩大。 2. They are planning a new campaign against corruption. 他们正在策划一个新的反贪污运动。 3. The campaign to seize the city was a failure. 攻占这个城市的战役失败了。 4. We were outmanoeuvred and outfought throughout the winter campaign. 我们在整个冬季战役中始终不如对手。 5. He announced that he would campaign for the senate. 他宣布他将参加议员竞选。', '名词: campaigner 过去式: campaigned 过去分词: campaigned 现在分词: campaigning 第三人称单数: campaigns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('auditor', '[\'ɔːdɪtər]', 'n.听者；稽核员', '1. I am a broadcasting auditor. 我是一名广播电台的听众。 2. The auditor looked through all the vouchers. 查帐员审核了全部凭单。 3. The auditor began the examination of accounts. 稽核员开始审察帐务。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pore', '[pɔːr]', 'n.毛孔；小孔 v.熟读；钻研；沉思', '1. He was sweating through every pore. 他每个毛孔都在冒汗。 2. Sweat exudes through the pores. 汗从毛孔中渗出。 3. Water seeped into the pores of the rock. 水迅速被岩石的空隙吸收。 4. He had spent several hours in the library poring over those musty documents. 他一连好几个小时呆在图书馆里仔细翻阅那些发霉味的文献资料。', '过去式: pored 过去分词: pored 现在分词: poring 第三人称单数: pores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defy', '[dɪ\'faɪ]', 'vt.藐视；挑衅；反抗', '1. The pine trees defy severe cold. 松树不畏严寒。 2. If you defy the law, you will be sent to prison. 如果你蔑视法律，你将被送入监狱。 3. He defined the order of the court. 他蔑视法庭的命令。 4. He won\'t allow anyone to defy his ministerial authority. 他不允许任何人挑衅他的教长权威。', '过去式: defied 过去分词: defied 现在分词: defying 第三人称单数: defies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anticipate', '[æn\'tɪsɪpeɪt]', 'vt.预期；提前使用；抢 ... 前 vi.预言', '1. We anticipate that we will meet a certain amount of resistance to our plan. 我们预料我们的计划会遇到一些人的反对。 2. I anticipate reading the book with great interest. 我以极大的兴趣期待着读这本书。 3. It is unwise to anticipate your earnings by spending a lot of money. 大量花钱提前使用自己的收入是不明智的。 4. They anticipate ours by just one month. 他们比我们抢先了一个月。', '形容词: anticipatable 名词: anticipator 过去式: anticipated 过去分词: anticipated 现在分词: anticipating 第三人称单数: anticipates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yeast', '[jiːst]', 'n.酵母；发酵剂 vi.发酵；起泡沫', '1. Yeast can be used in making beer and bread. 酵母可用于酿啤酒和发面包。 2. The excess yeast is saved for future use. 剩余的酵母粉被保留下来以备以后使用。 3. The quality of rapid-fermenting yeast would directly influence yellow rice wine fermentation and wine quality. 机械化速酿酒母生产为机械化黄酒大罐发酵的优良发酵剂。 4. I want to re-pitch yeast in a red fermentation. 我要再草地红色酵母发酵。', '过去式: yeasted 过去分词: yeasted 现在分词: yeasting 第三人称单数: yeasts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('considerate', '[kən\'sɪdərət]', 'adj.考虑周到的；体谅的；体贴的', '1. It was considerate of you to bring me my raincoat. 你为我带来雨衣,真是想得周到。 2. It is considerate of you to call on your relatives from time to time. 你时时拜望亲戚很周到啊。 3. He is no more considerate of others than his brother is. 他不体谅别人，就跟他弟弟一样。 4. She\'s a very considerate and caring person. 她是一个很懂得体贴和关心的人。', '副词: considerately 名词: considerateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dab', '[dæb]', 'v.轻触；轻涂 n.轻拍；少量；熟手；比目鱼', '1. Dab the coffee off with your handkerchief. 用你的手帕把咖啡擦掉。 2. You can dab at the stain on your coat with a wet towel. 你可以用湿毛巾在衣服的污迹处轻轻地擦几下。 3. Dab the solution on your scar to relieve the pain. 将药液涂在伤口上以缓解疼痛。 4. Again, try not to use too much water. Just dab the paint on. 这次也不要用太多的水。只涂上少量的颜料就可以了。 5. She gave me a dab with her umbrella. 她用雨伞轻轻拍了我一下。', '过去式: dabbed 过去分词: dabbed 现在分词: dabbing 第三人称单数: dabs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bizarre', '[bɪ\'zɑːr]', 'adj.奇异的；怪诞的', '1. The building was of bizarre construction. 这建筑构造奇异。 2. She got herself up in a bizarre outfit. 她穿了一套古怪的套装 3. Its bizarre quality was not lost on us. 我们没有被那种异乎寻常的气氛弄得晕头转向。 4. His bizarre behavior attracted our attention. 他怪诞的行为吸引了我们的注意力。', '副词: bizarrely 名词: bizarreness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prosecute', '[\'prɑːsɪkjuːt]', 'vt.起诉；告发；从事；彻底进行 vi.起诉；担任检察官', '1. Trespassers will be prosecuted. 闲人免进，违者必究。 2. He was prosecuted for exceeding the speed limit. 他被告发超速行驶。 3. He vowed that he would prosecute them for fraud. 他郑重宣布将起诉他们犯有欺诈罪。 4. We should never prosecute the innocent. 我们决不应控告无辜的人。 5. The police decided not to prosecute. 警方决定不予起诉。', '形容词: prosecutable 过去式: prosecuted 过去分词: prosecuted 现在分词: prosecuting 第三人称单数: prosecutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ambiguous', '[æm\'bɪɡjuəs]', 'adj.模棱两可的；含糊不清的', '1. He gave us an ambiguous answer . 他给了我们一个模棱两可的答复。 2. In fact, your ambiguous words amount to a refusal. 实际上,你说的那些模棱两可的话等于是拒绝。 3. Her account was deliberately ambiguous. 她的陈述故意含混不清。 4. Why are you always so ambiguous about this problem? 为什么你总是对这个问题含糊不清？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('illustrate', '[\'ɪləstreɪt]', 'vt.说明；（为书）作插图；图解 vi.举例说明；发亮', '1. He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point. 他指着图表来说明他的论点。 2. In this section, I\'ll illustrate some of these differences. 在这一节,我将举例说明一些不同之处。 3. Our textbook is very well illustrated. 我们的课本插图丰富。 4. This chart is used to illustrate all the changes. 这张图片用来解释所有的变化。', '形容词: illustratable 名词: illustrator 过去式: illustrated 过去分词: illustrated 现在分词: illustrating 第三人称单数: illustrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wistful', '[\'wɪstfl]', 'adj.渴望的；忧思的；留恋的', '1. The boy looks with wistful eyes at the toy on display. 那男孩看著展出的玩具，眼中流露出渴望的神情。 2. The poor mother has wistful reminiscences of her lost youth. 这个贫穷的母亲怅惘地回忆她已经逝去的青春。 3. His sole reference to Watergate was wistful. 他对水门事件的唯一反应就是陷入沉思。 4. She had a last wistful look at the house. 她留恋地最后朝那房子看了一眼。', '副词: wistfully 名词: wistfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('speedy', '[\'spiːdi]', 'adj.快速的；高速的；迅速的；敏捷的；立即的', '1. The speedy development makes that many firms search new outlets. 科学的快速发展促使许多企业探求新的出路。 2. His fidelity and industry brought him speedy promotion. 他的忠于职守和勤于工作使他得到迅速晋级。 3. The patient had a speedy revival after her operation. 那个女病人在手术后迅速康复。 4. The student\'s speedy answers were praised by the teacher. 这个学生敏捷的回答得到了老师的表扬。', '副词: speedily 比较级: speedier 最高级: speediest 名词: speediness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trickle', '[\'trɪkl]', 'vi.滴流；慢慢移动 n.细流；徐徐地流', '1. A river that flowed out of the lake was reduced to a trickle. 一条曾经从该湖流出的小河，现在已经变成了一条滴流。 2. Only a trickle of water came out of the pipe. 管子里淌出来的只是小小的细流。 3. No water to trickle down into the cabinets below. 没有水，以涓滴细流下来到机柜下面。', '过去式: trickled 过去分词: trickled 现在分词: trickling 第三人称单数: trickles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('austerity', '[ɔː\'sterəti]', 'n.节俭；苦行；(经济的)紧缩；严厉', '1. Austerity, not market reform, was his message. 节俭，而不是改革，才是他传递的信息。 2. Austerity is the only path to attain liberation. 苦修是通向解脱的唯一的道路。 3. Wartime austerities included food rationing and shortage of fuel. 战时的艰苦包括食物配给和燃料短缺。 4. Children are afraid of the austerity of their schoolmaster. 孩子们都害怕校长的严厉。', '名词复数: austerities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nationalism', '[\'næʃnəlɪzəm]', 'n.民族主义；爱国心；政治独立运动', '1. Nationalism was rapidly becoming a dangerous force. 民族主义迅速变为一股危险的势力。 2. Different people may have different definitions of nationalism at home and abroad. 国内外关于民族主义定义众说纷纭。 3. A truly global Internet will test our notions of nationalism. 真正的全球因特网将考验我们对于爱国主义的信念。', '形容词: nationalistic 副词: nationalistically 名词: nationalist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gleeful', '[\'ɡliːfl]', 'adj.愉快的；极快乐的', '1. I\'m gleeful to hear of the progress of you work. 我很高兴听说你的工作取得新进展。 2. Mr.Smith was gleeful over the achievement they had made. 史密斯先生对他们取得的成就感到万分高兴。', '副词: gleefully 名词: gleefulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('loan', '[loʊn]', 'n.贷款；借出 v.借；供应货款', '1. The bank will accommodate him with a loan. 银行将向他提供一笔贷款。 2. I propose to repay the loan at 20 pounds a month. 我打算每月偿还贷款20英镑。 3. She offered me the loan of her car. 她提出把汽车借给我用。 4. I have the book out on loan from the library. 我从图书馆里借出那本书。 5. Can I loan a ladder from you for a day or so? 我可以借你的梯子用一两天吗?', '名词: loaner 过去式: loaned 过去分词: loaned 现在分词: loaning 第三人称单数: loans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('librarian', '[laɪ\'breriən]', 'n.图书管理员；图书馆学专家；图书馆馆长', '1. The librarian saved the rare books from the fire. 这位图书管理员从火中救出了一些珍本书。', '名词: librarianship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('balmy', '[\'bɑːmi]', 'adj.芳香的；温和的；<俚>疯狂的；古怪的', '1. We can still spray appropriately balmy agent or deodorant. 我们还可适当喷洒芳香剂或除臭剂。 2. The air was warm and balmy. 天气温暖宜人。 3. This balmy weather is a herald of spring. 这种温和的天气是春天的预兆。 4. I’m sure the neighbours must have thought I was balmy yelling about shoes! 我敢说邻居们一定以为我是在冲鞋子大吼大叫呢！', '副词: balmily 比较级: balmier 最高级: balmiest 名词: balminess');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('generalize', '[\'dʒenrəlaɪz]', 'v.概括；归纳；使一般化', '1. It is dangerous to generalize about people. 以偏概全地谈论人是危险的。 2. You cannot generalize about the effects of the drug from one or two cases. 不能根据一两个病例就得出该药是否有效的结论。 3. It is difficult to generalize about job trends in the West. 对西方的就业趋势做一个归纳概括并非易事。 4. Don\'t generalize a conclusion from a few examples. 不要从几个事例中归纳出结论。', '过去式: generalized 过去分词: generalized 现在分词: generalizing 第三人称单数: generalizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('illustrious', '[ɪ\'lʌstriəs]', 'adj.著名的；杰出的', '1. He studied painting under illustrious masters. 他在著名大师的指导下学画。 2. Don\'t pull your illustrious past on me. 别把你那辉煌的过去灌输给我啦。 3. Washington and Lincoln are illustrious Americans. 华盛顿和林肯都是杰出的美国人。 4. His illustrious accomplishments made him one of the greatest men in this century. 他的杰出成就使他成为本世纪最伟大的人物之一。', '副词: illustriously 名词: illustriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seismograph', '[\'saɪzməɡræf]', 'n.地动仪；测振仪', '1. China\'s Zhang Heng invented the seismograph during the Han Dynasty. 中国的张衡在汉朝时发明了地动仪。 2. People laughed at Zhang Heng when he first introduced his seismograph, and it was only later that the world recognized his greatness. 当初张衡发明出他的地动仪时，人们都在嘲笑他，只有后来全世界才意识到他的伟大。 3. Earthquakes are recorded with a seismometer, also known as a seismograph. 地震检波器，也被称为测振仪，可记录地震。', '形容词: seismographic 名词: seismographer');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mishap', '[\'mɪshæp]', 'n.不幸之事；灾祸；恶运', '1. Many species will be dwarfed due to this mishap. 许多物种都因这一灾祸而发育不良。 2. Your birth was no mistake or mishap, and your life is no fluke of nature. 你的出生不是一个错误或灾祸，你的生命也绝非侥幸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contemn', '[kən\'tem]', 'vt.侮辱；蔑视', '1. I contemn the people who treat children so cruelly. 我蔑视如此虐待孩子的人。', '名词: contemner 过去式: contemned 过去分词: contemned 现在分词: contemning 第三人称单数: contemns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gild', '[ɡɪld]', 'v.镀金；虚饰 n.协会；行会（=guild)', '1. The setting sun gilds the sky. 落日把天空染成金色。 2. Her beauty gilds her vice. 她的美貌掩盖了她的邪恶。 3. For such a beautiful girl, to use make-up would be to gild the lily. 对一个这样漂亮的女孩来说，化妆有些画蛇添足。', '名词: gilder 过去式: gilded/gilt 过去分词: gilded/gilt 现在分词: gilding 第三人称单数: gilds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amuse', '[ə\'mjuːz]', 'v.娱乐；消遣；使 ... 发笑', '1. I amuse myself by reading on weekends. 周末我读书消遣。 2. It is not always easy to amuse oneself on holiday. 让自己在假期里自娱并不总是容易的。 3. The boys amuse themselves by drawing caricatures of their teacher. 男孩子们以画老师的漫画取乐。 4. He could amuse us for hours with his stories of the theater. 他能接连几小时地为我们讲戏剧故事逗我们发笑。', '形容词: amusable 名词: amuser 过去式: amused 过去分词: amused 现在分词: amusing 第三人称单数: amuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('captivity', '[kæp\'tɪvəti]', 'n.囚禁；被俘；束缚', '1. He had been kept in captivity for a month. 他被囚禁了一个月。 2. They prayed for an early deliverance from captivity. 他们为早日获释而祈祷。 3. He was released from his long captivity. 他被释放了，结束了他长期的被俘生活。 4. Captivity of itself is not a condition of culpability. 被俘本身不是应受惩罚的行为。', '名词复数: captivities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trend', '[trend]', 'n.趋势；倾向；方位 vi.倾向；转向', '1. The trend of prices is still upward. 物价仍有上涨趋势。 2. The youth like to follow the latest trends in fashion. 年轻人喜好追求最新的流行款式。 3. This quartet represents a major new trend in modern music. 这首四重奏的曲子反映了现代音乐中一种主要的新趋向。 4. The event changed the trend of public opinion. 这件事改变了舆论的趋向。 5. The prices of houses are trending upwards. 房价趋于上涨。', '过去式: trended 过去分词: trended 现在分词: trending 第三人称单数: trends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ceaseless', '[\'siːsləs]', 'adj.不绝的；不停的', '1. It must be wielded in spite of the ceaseless, howling protests of the wicked. 它必须在不绝的怨恨以及咆哮邪恶的抗议中的得以运用。 2. His ceaseless chatter began to annoy me. 他不停的唠叨使我厌烦起来。 3. The girl\'s ceaseless cry makes us feel pity for her. 这个小女孩不停的哭声使我们对她感到同情。', '副词: ceaselessly 名词: ceaselessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('innovation', '[ˌɪnə\'veɪʃn]', 'n.创新；革新', '1. There is no end to practice or innovation. 实践永无止境,创新永无止境。 2. In the age of global competition, design innovation is vital. 在全球激烈竞争的时代,设计创新至关重要。 3. It was a period of innovation. 这是革新时期。 4. A surge of innovation in techniques is on the horizon. 技术改进的浪潮即将出现。', '形容词: innovational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ranch', '[ræntʃ]', 'n.牧场', '1. It\'s about 50 kilometers from here to my ranch. 从这儿到我的牧场约有五十公里。 2. The ranch boards vacationers during the summer. 牧场夏天为度假者提供收费膳宿。', '过去式: ranched 过去分词: ranched 现在分词: ranching 第三人称单数: ranches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('malady', '[\'mælədi]', 'n.病；疾病；弊病', '1. There is no specific remedy for the malady. 没有医治这种病的特效药。 2. The boy is suffering from some strange malady. 这男孩患了某种奇怪的病。 3. I doubt that I shall ever be cured of this malady. 我怀疑自己是否能够从这种疾病中康复。 4. They are managing to control the malady into a small range. 他们设法将疾病控制在小范围之内。', '名词复数: maladies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suspect', '[sə\'spekt]', 'v.怀疑；猜想 n.嫌疑犯 adj.可疑的；不可信的', '1. They suspected an ambush. 他们怀疑有埋伏。 2. I suspect he was lying by the boy\'s abnormal behaviour. 从那个男孩的反常举动中,我怀疑他在撒谎。 3. Just at that time, I began to suspect whether to tell her that matter. 只是在那个时候,我开始怀疑我是否应该告诉她那件事。 4. She has more intelligence than we suspected her to possess. 她的智慧比我们猜想的要高。 5. He\'s a prime suspect in the murder case. 他是这次谋杀案的主要怀疑对象 6. His motives are highly suspect. 他的动机是高度令人生疑的。', '过去式: suspected 过去分词: suspected 现在分词: suspecting 第三人称单数: suspects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lens', '[lenz]', 'n.镜头；镜片；透镜；(眼球的)水晶体 v.给…摄影；给…拍照', '1. Don\'t smear the lens; I\'ve just polished it. 别把镜头弄脏了，我刚刚擦过。 2. Some adjustment of the lens may be necessary. 可能有必要调节一下镜头。 3. The camera lens must be screened from direct sunlight. 照相机的镜头不可受到阳光的直射。 4. He uses lens to make things appear clearer. 他用镜片以便看东西更清楚些。', '形容词: lensed 名词复数: lenses 过去式: lensed 过去分词: lensed 现在分词: lensing 第三人称单数: lenses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ferocious', '[fə\'roʊʃəs]', 'adj.残忍的；凶猛的；极度的', '1. The ferocious chieftain was executed. 那个凶残的匪首被处决了。 2. I could catch the glare of their ferocious eyes. 我连它们那残忍的眼睛中的灼灼目光都看清楚了。 3. Both tigers and leopards are ferocious beasts. 虎豹都是凶猛的野兽。 4. The oncoming force of the typhoon was ferocious. 这次台风来势凶猛。', '副词: ferociously 名词: ferociousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('microorganism', '[ˌmaɪkroʊ\'ɔːgənˌɪzəm]', 'n.微生物', '1. Bacteria belong to the microorganism. 细菌属于微生物。 2. This microorganism is a producer of disease. 该微生物是疾病制造者。 3. A microorganism is too small to see with the naked eye. 微生物太小,不能用肉眼看见。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blemish', '[\'blemɪʃ]', 'n.瑕疵；污点；缺点 v.玷污；损害', '1. These wine glasses were sold at half price because of blemishes in the jade. 这些酒杯半价出售，因为玉上有瑕疵。 2. There is a blemish in the swimming suit. 这件游泳衣上有个污点。 3. That mole is a blemish on his face. 那个黑痣是他脸上的缺点。 4. His reputation was blemished by a newspaper article alleging he had taken bribes. 报纸上一篇文章说他受贿，他的声誉因此受到玷污。', '名词: blemisher 过去式: blemished 过去分词: blemished 现在分词: blemishing 第三人称单数: blemishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foster', '[\'fɔːstər]', 'vt.领养；培养；促进；鼓励；抱有（希望等） adj.收养的', '1. People who cannot have a baby of their own sometimes foster (a child). 不能生育的人有时领养别人的(孩子). 2. It is very important to foster an interest. 培养一种兴趣是十分重要的。 3. The mother tried to foster her son\'s interest in music. 母亲设法培养儿子对音乐的兴趣。 4. Ignorance fosters superstition. 无知助长迷信。 5. The foster children also deserve love and care. 收养的孩子也应该得到关爱。', '过去式: fostered 过去分词: fostered 现在分词: fostering 第三人称单数: fosters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('valor', '[\'vælə]', 'n.英勇；勇猛', '1. His valor in the war was seen by everybody. 他在战争中的英勇人所共见。 2. The king knighted the soldier for his valor. 国王因那位军人英勇而封他为爵士。 3. They owed their lives to the valor of the firemen. 他们将其生命归功于消防员的英勇。 4. Fortitude is distinct from valor. 刚毅与勇猛不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cryptic', '[\'krɪptɪk]', 'adj.隐秘的；秘密的；用密码的；隐晦的', '1. A cryptic message said France needs to pull troops out of Afghanistan. 一个神秘消息要求法国需要从阿富汗撤军。 2. I don\'t know what this cryptic remark is intended to convey. 我不知道这句暗藏玄机的评语是要表示什麽。 3. Before the day was over, Henry issued a cryptic memo to top executives. 亨利赶着在当天就向高级职员发出了一份使人费解的内部通知。 4. She made a cryptic comment about how the film mirrored her life. 她隐晦地表示说这部电影是她人生的写照。', '副词: cryptically 异体字: cryptical 名词: crypticness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gap', '[ɡæp]', 'n.缺口；裂缝；差距；空白', '1. He has a gap between his two front teeth. 他的两个门牙之间有一缺口。 2. A big gap yawned between the rocks. 岩石间豁开一个大裂口。 3. They planed to narrow the gap between imports and exports. 他们计划缩小进出口的差额。 4. Reducing the gap between rich and poor is one of the main challenges facing the government. 缩小贫富之间的差距是政府面临的主要难题之一。', '过去式: gapped 过去分词: gapped 现在分词: gapping 第三人称单数: gaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fragment', '[\'fræɡmənt]', 'n.碎片；片段 v.使破碎；分裂', '1. She dropped the vase on the floor and it broke into fragments. 她把花瓶掉在地上，摔成了碎片。 2. There\'s a fragment of glass in the wound. 伤口内有玻璃碎片。 3. Her hand was cut by a fragment of glass. 她的手被一块玻璃碎片划破了。 4. I overheard a fragment of their conversation. 我无意中听到他们谈话的片段。 5. These bullets fragment on impact. 这些子弹射中物体时爆炸成碎片。', '过去式: fragmented 过去分词: fragmented 现在分词: fragmenting 第三人称单数: fragments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diplomatic', '[ˌdɪplə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.外交的；古字体的；老练的', '1. He has diplomatic immunity. 他有外交豁免权。 2. The exercise of patience is essential in diplomatic negotiations. 在外交谈判中，重要的是要有耐性。 3. He tried to be diplomatic when he refused their invitation. 他在拒绝他们的邀请时，尽可能地婉转些。 4. John was as diplomatic as Mary when talking to the press. 约翰在与媒体打交道时和玛丽一样老练。', '副词: diplomatically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hammer', '[\'hæmər]', 'n.锤；榔头 vi.锤击；反复敲打 vt.锤打；严厉批评', '1. He hit the nail into the wall with a hammer. 他用一把锤子把钉子打进墙里去。 2. He smashed a hole in the window with a hammer. 他用锤子在玻璃上打了个洞。 3. He took a hammer and recessed a hole into the wall. 他拿起一个榔头，在墙上敲出一个洞。 4. He dashed into the porch and began to hammer on the door. 他冲上门廊用力捶起门来。 5. The police hammered the door. 警察不停地敲门。', '名词: hammerer 过去式: hammered 过去分词: hammered 现在分词: hammering 第三人称单数: hammers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contour', '[\'kɑːntʊr]', 'n.周线；轮廓；等高线；概要；电路 vt.画轮廓(画等高线) adj.显示轮廓的', '1. The set of edges which bound the region is the contour of the region. 包围某区域的边的集合称为区域的周线。 2. The contour of that mountain looks like a dragon. 那座大山的轮廓看上去像一条龙。 3. The smooth contour of the sculpture is wonderful. 雕塑物平滑的轮廓线简直太美了。 4. The figure shows a part of a contour map. 附图是一幅等高线地图的一部分。 5. Could you contour the mountain? 你能把这座山的等高线画出来吗？ 6. Please show me the contour map. 请把等高线地图给我看看。', '过去式: contoured 过去分词: contoured 现在分词: contouring 第三人称单数: contours');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('radical', '[\'rædɪkl]', 'adj.激进的；彻底的；基本的 n.激进分子', '1. I know you are radical in your thinking, but don\'t go too far. 我知道你思想激进,但不要走的太远。 2. He took up a radical position on this issue. 他对这个问题抱着激进的态度。 3. They called for a radical reform of our tax system. 他们要求对税收制度进行根本改革。 4. Lambert did not reach the more radical conclusion. 兰伯特还没有达到更本质的结论。 5. Ted is a fire-eating radical. 泰德是个咄咄逼人的激进份子。', '副词: radically 名词: radicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('loop', '[luːp]', 'n.环；圈；回路；环形线路 vt.以圈结；以环连结；使 ... 成环（圈） vi.形成环；环形运动', '1. This control may be closed loop or open loop. 控制可以是闭环的也可以是开环的。 2. Her wavy hair fell in loose wisps and loops upon her shoulders. 她那一头波浪般的长发一簇簇一圈圈地散垂在肩上。 3. He looped a scarf around his neck. 他把围巾在脖子上围成一圈。 4. I have to loop the wooden pegs around the garden. 我不得不用木桩来环住园地。', '过去式: looped 过去分词: looped 现在分词: looping 第三人称单数: loops');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('specimen', '[\'spesɪmən]', 'n.标本；样本', '1. This specimen is richly variegated in colour. 这件标本上有很多颜色。 2. Arthur brought out his specimen box. 亚瑟拿出了他的标本箱。 3. He is still a fine specimen of health. 他仍是健康的典范。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glacial', '[\'ɡleɪʃl]', 'adj.冰川(期)的；非常冷的；缓慢的；(人)态度不友善的', '1. Recent glacial recession is alarming to scientists. 最近的冰川缩减令科学家震惊。 2. Newly installed seismometers will listen for glacial earthquakes. 新安装的地震仪将可监听冰河地震的声音。 3. It was a door even more glacial than that of winter which was ajar. 比起平时冬季的那扇半开的门,这扇门更冻人。 4. Work proceeded at a glacial pace. 工作以极缓慢的速度进行着。', '副词: glacially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('salon', '[sə\'lɑːn]', 'n.美容院；沙龙；美术展览馆；客厅', '1. I went to the salon to dress my hair for the dance. 我去美容院做头发，以便参加舞会。 2. Our salon is well-lit and clean. 我们的美容院又亮又干净。 3. I used to go to English salon on Sundays. 我以前常在周日去参加英语沙龙。 4. You can hear a lot of dirt at a salon. 你在沙龙上会听到很多流言蜚语。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yearn', '[jɜːrn]', 'v.渴望；想念；盼望；同情', '1. He yearned to return to his native land. 他渴望回到故乡。 2. He yearned for a sight of the old, familiar faces. 他渴望一见那些熟悉的老面孔。 3. The child yearns much toward his friends. 那小孩很想念他的朋友。 4. They yearned for his return. 他们盼望着他回来。', '副词: yearningly 名词: yearner 过去式: yearned 过去分词: yearned 现在分词: yearning 第三人称单数: yearns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laboratory', '[\'læbrətɔːri]', 'n.实验室', '1. They need one laboratory technician. 他们需要一名实验室技术员。 2. The school has a large biological laboratory. 这所学校有一个很大的生物实验室。 3. The product is on trial in our laboratory. 该产品正在由我们实验室做测试。 4. The students will have an experiment in the laboratory tomorrow. 学生们明天要在实验室里做实验。', '名词复数: laboratories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emotion', '[ɪ\'moʊʃn]', 'n.情感；感情；情绪', '1. Love, joy, hate, fear and grief are all emotions. 爱、喜、恨、惧、悲都是情感。 2. The speaker appealed to our emotions rather than to our minds. 演讲者激发了我们的情感而不是启发我们的思考。 3. I hate this kind of cheap emotion. 我讨厌这种肤浅的感情。 4. Chopin aroused very complicated emotions in her. 肖邦的乐曲唤起了她极其复杂的感情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forecast', '[\'fɔːrkæst]', 'n.预测；预报 v.预测', '1. Share prices plunged as a result of the gloomy economic forecast. 关于经济前景暗淡的预测导致股票价格大跌。 2. The Treasury\'s forecast assumes that inflation will remain below 3%. 财政部的预测称,通货膨胀率将保持在3%25以下。 3. The weather forecast says it will be sunny tomorrow. 天气预报说明天是晴天。 4. Despite the good weather forecast, the next morning was as wet as ever. 尽管预报称天气很好，但次日上午仍阴雨绵绵。 5. They tried to forecast the result of the football match. 他们试图预测这场足球比赛的结果。', '形容词: forecastable 名词: forecaster 过去式: forecast/forecasted 过去分词: forecast/forecasted 现在分词: forecasting 第三人称单数: forecasts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corrosion', '[kə\'rəʊʒn]', 'n.侵蚀；腐蚀；锈蚀', '1. They are sprayed with oil to prevent corrosion. 它们被喷了油以防止侵蚀。 2. Some substances resist corrosion by air or water. 有些物质可以抗空气或水的腐蚀。 3. Clean off any corrosion before applying the paint. 先除去所有的锈迹再上油漆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('antagonism', '[æn\'tæɡənɪzəm]', 'n.对抗；对立；敌对状态（行为）', '1. It may be regarded as an example of antagonism. 这可看作是对抗效应。 2. They tolerated their new neighbors, there was no antagonism. 他们对他们的新邻居很容忍，所以没有产生任何对抗状态。 3. You could sense the antagonism between them. 你能觉察出他们之间有对立情绪。 4. Let us examine both sides of this antagonism. 让我们来看看这种对立的两个方面吧。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('colloquial', '[kə\'loʊkwiəl]', 'adj.口语的；会话的', '1. Colloquial expression is an important property of spoken English. 口语惯用语是英语口语的一个重要组成部分。', '副词: colloquially 名词: colloquialness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('silica', '[\'sɪlɪkə]', 'n.硅石；矽土', '1. Silica, in fact, is a desirable impurity because it is one of the reactants. 硅石实际上是一种有用的杂质，因为它是一种反应剂。 2. Our company has our own silia stone moutain and silica powder producing plant. 我公司有自己的硅石矿山和硅石粉加工厂。 3. The government sets up new health standard for respirable silica dust in the air of workplace. 政府出台了新的工作场所空气呼吸性矽尘卫生标准。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compile', '[kəm\'paɪl]', 'vt.编译；编制；编纂', '1. Your first program is ready to compile and run. 你的第一个程序可以编译和运行了。 2. We are trying to compile a list of suitable people for the job. 我们在努力编制一份适合做这项工作的人员的名单。 3. How do we compile a balance of payments statements? 我们如何编制收支平衡表? 4. It takes many years of hard work to compile a good dictionary. 编纂一部好词典要花多年心血。', '过去式: compiled 过去分词: compiled 现在分词: compiling 第三人称单数: compiles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excellent', '[\'eksələnt]', 'adj.杰出的；优秀的；极好的', '1. She would have made an excellent teacher. 她本可以成为杰出的教师。 2. As soon as she learns the office routine, she will be an excellent assistant. 她一旦熟悉了办公室的日常事务,就会成为一名优秀的助手。 3. Hawaii is an excellent tourist resort. 夏威夷是极好的旅游胜地。 4. He worked out an excellent idea. 他想出了一个极好的主意。', '副词: excellently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eclipse', '[ɪ\'klɪps]', 'n.日或月食；丧失；没落 vt.形成日或月食；使 ... 黯然失色', '1. It will take an hour to reach full eclipse stage. 从月食到全食历时一个小时。 2. It was reported that there would be a lunar eclipse tomorrow evening. 据报道说，明天晚上有月食。 3. The moon is partly eclipsed. 月偏食了。 4. It was reported that there would be an annular eclipse tomorrow. 据报道说，明天有日环食。 5. Its economy may well eclipse Japan\'s in size in 20 years or so.\" 中国经济的规模在20年左右的时间里完全可能超过日本。', '过去式: eclipsed 过去分词: eclipsed 现在分词: eclipsing 第三人称单数: eclipses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recall', '[rɪ\'kɔːl]', 'n.回忆；取消；召回 vt.召回；恢复；回想起；唤起；与 ... 相似', '1. Do you have any recall of that meeting? 你还记得那次会见吗? 2. The new law is now established beyond recall. 新法律现已制定，不得撤销。 3. The experiment sample the raw test of novel Hero Borns to test for times , and it acquires an accuracy of 86.93% , while an recall rate of 91.83%. 实验对小说《英雄出世》的生文本进行了多次抽样测试 4. With the impulse of \"mercantile system\", the Occident adjust their policy one after the other, recall Jew in succession. 在“重商主义”政策的积极推动下,西欧各国相继调整对犹政策,纷纷召回犹太人。', '形容词: recallable 过去式: recalled 过去分词: recalled 现在分词: recalling 第三人称单数: recalls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('X-ray', '[\'eksreɪ]', 'n.X射线；光机；X光照片 vt.用X射线检查', '1. When will I know the result of my x ray? 我何时可以知道X光检查的结果? 2. X ray is increasingly used in industry as well. 在工业中X射线也得到了广泛应用。 3. The x ray show a fractured ankle. X 光片显示足踝骨折。 4. You shall have an x ray examination. 你应该作X光检查。', '过去式: x-rayed/X-rayed 过去分词: x-rayed/X-rayed 现在分词: x-raying/X-raying 第三人称单数: x-rays/X-rays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hearsay', '[\'hɪrseɪ]', 'n.传闻', '1. Hearsay definitely can\'t be regarded as accurate information. 道听途说的决然不能算作很准确的消息。 2. I knew by hearsay that he was the editor of the American Mercury. 我听说他是《美国信使》的编辑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vigorous', '[\'vɪɡərəs]', 'adj.精力充沛的；有力的；元气旺盛的', '1. Old as he is, he is none the less vigorous and active. 虽然他年纪很大了，他仍然精力充沛。 2. He never ceased to chase after his dream in his vigorous youth. 在精力充沛的年轻时代他从未停止过追求自己的梦想。 3. She gave the floor a vigorous sponge all over. 她用海绵把地板 使劲儿擦了一遍。 4. He uttered several vigorous expletives when he dropped the iron on his foot. 他的熨斗掉下砸在脚上，他随口骂了几声。', '副词: vigorously 名词: vigorousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mangle', '[\'mæŋɡl]', 'v.碾压；损坏；糟蹋；乱切 n.碾压机', '1. New shoes don\'t cut, blister, or mangle his feet. 新鞋子不会硌脚，起泡，或让脚受伤。 2. The symphony was dreadfully mangled. 那首交响乐曲给糟蹋得不成样子。 3. The plane is late; it is going to mangle your schedule for the day. 航班延误了，而它将影响你一整天的行程。', '名词: mangler 过去式: mangled 过去分词: mangled 现在分词: mangling 第三人称单数: mangles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fray', '[freɪ]', 'v.恼火；紧张 v.磨损 n.吵闹；吵架；争斗 n.磨损处', '1. Tempers began to fray in the hot weather. 大热天脾气烦燥。 2. As the debate went on, tempers began to fray. 随着辩论的继续，火气就上来了。 3. Her nerves were frayed by the noises in the street. 街上的噪音使她神经紧张。 4. After spending a day with screaming children, her nerves were frayed. 与吵吵嚷嚷的孩子们呆了一天后,她的神经快要崩溃了。 5. The electric wire is fraying and could be dangerous to handle. 电线快磨破了，使用起来可能有危险。 6. The two gangsters seem to be eager for the fray. 那两个歹徒似乎唯恐不乱。', '过去式: frayed 过去分词: frayed 现在分词: fraying 第三人称单数: frays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resemble', '[rɪ\'zembl]', 'v.与…相似；像', '1. The brothers resemble each other in taste. 那对兄弟兴趣相似。 2. She resembles her sister in appearance but not in character. 她和她姐姐外貌相似，但性格不同。 3. You resemble your mother very closely. 你非常像你的母亲。', '名词: resembler 过去式: resembled 过去分词: resembled 现在分词: resembling 第三人称单数: resembles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mission', '[\'mɪʃn]', 'n.使命；代表团；任务；布道', '1. The minister was sent to Spain on mission. 这位部长奉命前往西班牙。 2. My mission in life is to help poor people. 我的天职是帮助穷人。 3. A Chinese trade mission has been dispatched to Japan. 一个中国贸易代表团已被派往日本。 4. Her mission was to reclaim former criminals. 她的任务是感化过去的罪犯。', '形容词: missional 过去式: missioned 过去分词: missioned 现在分词: missioning 第三人称单数: missions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slippery', '[\'slɪpəri]', 'adj.滑的；狡猾的；不可靠的', '1. A wet road is usually slippery. 潮湿的路往往是滑的。 2. The road was slippery after the rain. 下雨之后道路很滑。 3. Don\'t lend any money to that slippery person. 不要借钱给那个狡猾的家伙。 4. The England striker says the slippery Portuguese winker got him sent off in Saturday\'s World Cup clash. 英格兰前锋说这个狡猾的葡萄牙人在周六的比赛中迫使自己下场后挤眉弄眼。', '比较级: slipperier 最高级: slipperiest 名词: slipperiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exterminate', '[ɪk\'stɜːrmɪneɪt]', 'vt.消灭；扑灭；根绝', '1. This spray will exterminate the termites. 这种喷剂能消灭白蚁。 2. We must exterminate every mistake. 我们必须消除一切错误。 3. Taiwan\'s government has made it a priority to exterminate the fire ants. 台湾政府已将扑杀火蚁列为第一要务。 4. Would Mother Nature really exterminate mankind? 大自然会根除人类吗？', '形容词: exterminative 名词: extermination 过去式: exterminated 过去分词: exterminated 现在分词: exterminating 第三人称单数: exterminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chaos', '[\'keɪɑːs]', 'n.混乱；无秩序；混沌', '1. The wintry weather has caused chaos on the roads. 因风雪交加,道路上混乱不堪。 2. After the failure of the electricity supplies, the city was in chaos. 电力供应中断,城市陷于混乱之中。 3. Without rules, people would live in a state of chaos. 若无规则,人们将在混乱状态中生活。 4. Chaos often breeds life, when order breeds habit. 混沌常常孕育着生命，而秩序会产生习惯。', '形容词: chaotic 副词: chaotically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stamina', '[\'stæmɪnə]', 'n.精力；活力；耐力 n.[植]雄蕊 名词stamen的复数形式.', '1. He doesn\'t have the stamina to be a teacher. 他没有当教师的精力。 2. It\'s no wonder you\'ve got so much stamina. 难怪你精力这么充沛。 3. Currently, this region\'s economic development continues to maintain growth stamina. 目前，该地区经济发展继续保持增长活力。 4. He runs every day to hone his stamina. 为了增强耐力，他每天都进行跑步锻炼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rapture', '[\'ræptʃər]', 'n.狂喜 v.使狂喜', '1. He fall into rapture over classic music. 他对古典音乐喜爱若狂。 2. We are in raptures over the new books. 我们十分喜爱这些新书。 3. The mother gazed with rapture at her new born baby. 母亲着迷地凝视着她刚出生的婴儿。', '过去式: raptured 过去分词: raptured 现在分词: rapturing 第三人称单数: raptures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slovenly', '[\'slʌvnli]', 'adj.不修边幅的；邋遢的', '1. He had no dealings with those slovenly easy riders. 他不与那些不修边幅，到处闲荡的人打交道。 2. Better a bachelor s life than a slovenly wife. 过光棍生活，胜过有一个邋遢老婆。 3. The dinner was served in a slovenly manner. 这顿饭潦草地开了出来。', '名词: slovenliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instinctive', '[ɪn\'stɪŋktɪv]', 'adj.本能的；天性的；直觉的', '1. He tried to conceal his instinctive revulsion at the idea. 他试图饰盖自己对这一想法本能的厌恶。 2. Perhaps an analogy with what happens to us when we visit the theater will make this instinctive correlation clearer. 也许将此与我们看戏时的情况相比可以把这种本能的联系说得更清楚些。 3. Was there a foundation for the tenuous, instinctive fears that I couldn\'t seem to shake? 能不能给这微妙的，直觉的恐惧下个定论让我不再忐忑不安？ 4. I think most of us have the instinctive ability to discern between the merely obsequious and the purely altruistic. 我想我们大部分人都可以直觉的辨认出逢迎谄媚和纯粹的利他行为。', '副词: instinctively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('domestic', '[də\'mestɪk]', 'adj.家庭的；国内的；驯养的 n.佣人；家仆', '1. The store deals in objects of domestic utility. 那家商店出售家庭用品。 2. My value for domestic tranquility should much exceed theirs. 我应该远比他们重视家庭的平静生活。 3. Washington responded by freezing the price of domestic oil. 华盛顿作出的反应是冻结国内的石油价格。 4. We adopt an active attitude towards drawing on overseas fund to make up for domestic fund shortage. 我们采取积极的态度吸引海外资金以弥补国内资金短缺。 5. His domestics are all in years. 他的佣人全都上了年纪。', '副词: domestically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dormant', '[\'dɔːrmənt]', 'adj.休眠的；睡眠的；静止的；潜伏的；匿名的；（动物等）冬眠的', '1. Many living things are dormant in winter. 很多生物到了冬季都休眠。 2. The professor would try to awake their dormant and sluggish faculties. 这位教授应该试图唤醒他们沉睡和懒散的天赋。 3. A dormant volcano may erupt after an interval. 睡眠状态的火山经过一段时间后还会喷发。 4. Many dormant branches of our organization are now springing to active life. 我们组织中有许多沉寂的部门现在突然活跃起来。', '名词: dormancy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('minimal', '[\'mɪnɪməl]', 'adj.最小的；最低限度的', '1. The work was carried out at minimal cost. 这项工作是以最少的开销完成的。 2. She gained only minimal recognition for her work. 她的工作仅仅得到极少的赞誉。 3. There is a minimal quantity of imperfection in the batch. 这批产品的残次品极少。 4. Fortunately, the storm only did minimal damage to the farmer\'s crops. 很幸运, 暴风雨只使农民的庄稼受到轻微的损害。', '副词: minimally 名词: minimality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('humiliate', '[hjuː\'mɪlieɪt]', 'vt.使 ... 蒙羞；使丢脸', '1. She was humiliated because her children behaved so badly. 她为她的孩子表现不好而感到羞辱。 2. Though I aim to defeat you, should I succeed, I will not humiliate you. 虽然我的目标是战胜你,但就算我胜利了,那并不会让你蒙羞。 3. The boy humiliate his parents by behaving badly in front of the guests. 那男孩在客人面前表现不好,使父母丢面子。 4. I didn\'t want to humiliate her in front of her colleagues. 我不想当着她同事们的面令她难堪。', '过去式: humiliated 过去分词: humiliated 现在分词: humiliating 第三人称单数: humiliates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('piracy', '[\'paɪrəsi]', 'n.盗版；剽窃；著作权侵害；海盗行为', '1. The government has taken measures to curb piracy. 政府为了阻止盗版行为采取了若干措施。 2. We are in favor of fighting against piracy. 我们支持打击盗版。 3. One of the best ways to get the message across, according to the group, is to work with creative people in local communities who are victims of piracy themselves. 根据小组所说，最好的传达信息的方式之一是与当地委员会有创造力的人一起合作，那些人是剽窃的受害者。 4. In New York, we dove into the topic of piracy and the impact it is having on the established media industry. 在纽约,我们引入了著作权侵害及其对传媒业产生的影响的主题。', '名词复数: piracies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chalk', '[tʃɔːk]', 'n.粉笔；白垩 v.用粉笔写；记录；使变白；归咎', '1. The teacher wrote on the blackboard with a piece of chalk. 老师用一支粉笔在黑板上写字。 2. The teacher\'s chalk grated on the blackboard. 老师的粉笔在黑板上发出刺耳的摩擦声。 3. My father said cement couldn\'t be made from chalk. 我父亲说水泥不能用白垩来制作。 4. The boys chalked out goalposts on the playground wall. 男孩子们在运动场的墙上用粉笔画上了球门柱。', '形容词: chalky 名词: chalkiness 过去式: chalked 过去分词: chalked 现在分词: chalking 第三人称单数: chalks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dank', '[dæŋk]', 'adj.阴湿的 n.潮湿；沼泽地', '1. The dark, dank cave gave me the willies. 这阴暗潮湿的山洞使我感到心惊肉跳。 2. The air was so dank that the smoke hung heavily. 空气十分潮湿，所以烟气沉重地悬浮着。 3. The basement in our house is dark and dank, so it is full of mold. 我们家的地下室又暗又潮湿，里面长满了霉。', '副词: dankly 比较级: danker 最高级: dankest 名词: dankness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('retail', '[\'riːteɪl]', 'n.零售 vt.零售；传述 adv.以零售形式', '1. They buy at wholesale and sell at retail. 他们大批地买进,再以零售方式卖出。 2. These biros retail at 70p. 这些圆珠笔零售价为70便士。 3. We should be able to retail most of these products to overseas customers. 我们应能够把这些产品的大部分卖给海外的顾客。 4. Who is responsible for retailing these rumors about him? 是谁散布这些有关他的流言蜚语的？', '名词: retailer 过去式: retailed 过去分词: retailed 现在分词: retailing 第三人称单数: retails');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('automobile', '[\'ɔːtəməbiːl]', 'n.汽车 adj.汽车的', '1. He huddled the children into the automobile. 他急急忙忙地把孩子们推进汽车。 2. We jacked the automobile in order to change a tire. 我们用千斤顶把汽车托起换个轮胎。 3. There will be an exhibition of the development of automobile industry in our country next week. 下星期将举办一个关于我国汽车工业发展的展览。 4. The cylinder is an important part for automobile engine. 气缸套是影响汽车发动机性能的重要零件。', '名词: automobilist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oppose', '[ə\'poʊz]', 'v.反对；对抗；使对立', '1. It was courageous of him to oppose his chief. 他敢反对他的上司，真是勇敢。 2. The rabbles met on the square to oppose their new mayor. 平民们在广场上集会反对他们的新市长。 3. They opposed the government\'s new policies. 他们反对政府的新政策。 4. We\'re firmly opposed to the practice of powerpolitics between nations. 我们强烈反对在国与国之间实行强权政治。', '名词: opposer 过去式: opposed 过去分词: opposed 现在分词: opposing 第三人称单数: opposes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hitherto', '[ˌhɪðər\'tuː]', 'adv.到目前为止；迄今', '1. Hitherto, this is the advanced method. 到目前为止，这是先进的方法。 2. Hitherto he had experienced no great success in his attempt. 到目前为止，他的这种尝试还没有取得任何重大的成功。 3. For hitherto though I have lost all my time. 迄今我虽然失去了全部的时日。 4. I had hitherto continued to board with Godfrey. 迄今我仍在戈费雷处用膳。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('uneven', '[ʌn\'iːvn]', 'adj.不平坦的；不均匀的；奇数的；不规律的', '1. The ground was muddy and uneven, but we toiled on. 地面泥泞不平，我们仍吃力地向前走。 2. The car bumped on the uneven surface of the gravel road. 汽车在高低不平的砾石路面上颠簸着。 3. Players complained about the uneven bounce of the tennis court. 运动员抱怨说网球场的反弹力不均匀。 4. His work has been rather uneven this year. 他的工作质量今年一直不规则。', '副词: unevenly 比较级: unevener 最高级: unevenest 名词: unevenness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attribute', '[\'ætrɪbjuːt]', 'vt.把 ... 归于 n.属性；标志；象征；特征', '1. Most historians attribute such declines to wars and conquests. 大多数的历史学家把这样的衰亡归于战争和征服。 2. Many people\'s success can be attributed to hard work and a bit of luck. 很多人的成功都可以归于勤奋加上一点儿运气。 3. Public perception can also create a legal right for an attribute of a product. 公众的认知也能为产品的某个属性创造法律权利。 4. The attribute that indicates that the same copy of a routine cannot be used by another task. 一种属性，表示某一例行程序的同一副本不能被另一个任务使用。', '形容词: attributable 名词: attributer 过去式: attributed 过去分词: attributed 现在分词: attributing 第三人称单数: attributes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revenue', '[\'revənuː]', 'n.税收；收入；税务局', '1. National tax revenue grew by a large margin every year. 国家税收连年大幅度增长。 2. The state does not collect enough revenue to cover its expenditure. 政府征收的税收不能满足支出。 3. Rent is one form of revenue. 房租是一种收入。 4. The document states that all revenue has to be declared to the tax office. 该文件规定必须向税务局申报所有收入。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ratify', '[\'rætɪfaɪ]', 'v.批准；认可', '1. They ratify the pact because they think it will bring peace. 他们批准了这项协定，因为他们认为它将能带来和平。 2. The government of Honduras refused to ratify the convention. 洪都拉斯政府拒不批准该约。 3. It would reinforce the tendency to use the UN to ratify the gains of surprise attack. 这会助长利用联合国使通过突然袭击的办法夺占的领土得到认可的倾向。 4. He said Lebanese President Emile Lahoud and his council are expected to ratify the plan during the coming week. 他说，黎巴嫩总统拉胡德和议会将在本星期认可这个计划。', '名词: ratifier 过去式: ratified 过去分词: ratified 现在分词: ratifying 第三人称单数: ratifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eternal', '[ɪ\'tɜːrnl]', 'adj.永久的；永恒的 n.永恒的事', '1. The price of liberty is eternal vigilance. 自由的代价是永久提高警惕。 2. The bad man will suffer eternal damnation. 坏人将会受到永远的惩罚。 3. He is, as it were, an eternal boy. 他好像是个永远年轻的小伙子。 4. She felt eternal gratitude to him for saving her life. 她终生感激他的救命之恩。 5. The eternal motion of the stars fascinated him. 星体永恒的运行使他著迷。', '副词: eternally 名词: eternality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exploit', '[ɪk\'splɔɪt]', 'vt.剥削；利用；开发；开拓 n.功绩；英勇行为', '1. The capitalists exploit the workers in order to maximize profits. 资本家剥削工人是为了使利润最大化。 2. You must exploit all your spare time to learn English. 你必须利用一切空闲时间来学习英语。 3. People should read the related regulations before they exploit natural resources. 在开发自然资源前，人们应该先了解相关的规定。 4. We should look for blank parts in the market and exploit new market continuously. 我们应找准市场空白,不断开拓新市场。 5. Great men are remembered for their notable exploits. 伟人们因其丰功伟绩而被世人铭记。', '形容词: exploitable 副词: exploitatively 名词: exploitability 过去式: exploited 过去分词: exploited 现在分词: exploiting 第三人称单数: exploits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('malice', '[\'mælɪs]', 'n.恶意；怨恨；蓄意 [律]预谋.', '1. I know you bear no malice towards me. 我知道你对我毫无恶意。 2. There was a spice of malice in his words. 他的话中带有几分恶意。 3. It seems so absurd to bear malice after all that. 经过这一切之后还抱有怨恨情绪是很荒谬的。 4. His expression changed from kindness to malice. 他的表情从和蔼可亲变成满腔怨恨。 5. She did not trip Rose up accidentally, it was done with malice aforethought. 她并不是无意中把罗斯绊倒的，她这样做是有预谋的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plump', '[plʌmp]', 'adj.丰满的 v.下降；支持；变丰满 n.突然重重落下（的声音） adv.骤降；直接地', '1. The baby is plump and very cute. 那个婴儿白白胖胖的，十分可爱。 2. She is too plump to fit into this dress. 她太富态了，穿不下这件衣服。 3. Special injections can make lips look attractively young and plump. 注射特殊药物可使嘴唇年轻饱满，更加迷人。 4. The ducklings plumped into the water. 小鸭们突然跳进水中。 5. He told me plump that he would not give in. 他直截了当告诉我,他决不让步。', '形容词: plumpish 副词: plumply 比较级: plumper 最高级: plumpest 名词: plumpness 过去式: plumped 过去分词: plumped 现在分词: plumping 第三人称单数: plumps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('timber', '[\'tɪmbər]', 'n.木材；木料', '1. He used to be a timber merchant. 他曾是一个木材商。 2. Seasoned timber does not warp. 经干燥处理的木材不会翘曲。 3. The farmer spent a day in the woods hewing timber. 这个农夫花了一天时间在森林里砍木材。 4. We are making a bed from scrap timber. 我们在用碎木料做一张床。', '过去式: timbered 过去分词: timbered 现在分词: timbering 第三人称单数: timbers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rug', '[rʌɡ]', 'n.地毯；毯子；旅行毯', '1. Look at the holes that have been worn in this rug. 瞧瞧这块小地毯上磨出的洞。 2. I slid the rug in front of the fire. 我挪了挪铺在炉前的地毯。 3. Bind the edge of the rug so that it won\'t ravel. 给地毯镶个边以免开线。 4. The rug singed because it was too near the fire. 地毯太靠近壁炉已烤焦了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pupil', '[\'pjuːpl]', 'n.小学生；弟子；【解】瞳孔', '1. The headmaster has made a decision of suspension of a pupil from school. 校长已经做出对一名学生停学处分的决定。 2. A teacher can\'t give individual attention to each pupil if his class is large. 如果班上的人数多，老师就不能给予个别辅导了。 3. The painting is the work of a pupil of Rembrandt. 这幅画是伦勃朗的一位弟子的作品。 4. The tenor was a pupil of Caruso. 这位男高音歌手师承卡鲁索。', '形容词: pupilar');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tangible', '[\'tændʒəbl]', 'adj.可触摸的；实际的；有形的；确凿的', '1. It is the only tangible object the astronomer can handle. 这是天文学家能够掌握的唯一可接触的对象。 2. The tension between them was almost tangible. 他们之间的紧张关系几乎让人都感觉得出来。 3. The plan brought few tangible benefits to the poor. 这个计划没有给穷人带来多少实际好处。 4. Fossils give us tangible evidence that dinosaurs really existed. 化石给了我们恐龙确实存在的确切证据。', '副词: tangibly 名词: tangibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incursion', '[ɪn\'kɜːrʒn]', 'n.侵犯；入侵', '1. I resent these incursions upon my leisure time. 屡次侵占我的闲暇时间，我很反感。 2. They were outraged by our incursion into Cambodia. 他们对我们入侵柬埔寨感到愤慨。 3. It\'s a technically incursion and it\'s not an incursion of such. 这是一个技术上的进入，而不是真正的入侵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recognize', '[\'rekəɡnaɪz]', 'vt.承认；认出；意识到；表示感激；识别', '1. His thorough knowledge and competence were recognized. 他的渊博的学识和工作能力得到了承认。 2. I recognize your right to ask that question. 我承认你有权提出这个问题。 3. Can you recognize her from this picture? 你能从这张照片中认出她吗？ 4. He has the good sense to recognize a good man. 他真是慧眼识真才。', '形容词: recognizable 副词: recognizably 名词: recognizer 过去式: recognized 过去分词: recognized 现在分词: recognizing 第三人称单数: recognizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contemporary', '[kən\'tempəreri]', 'adj.同时代的；当代的 n.同时代的人；同龄人', '1. Marlowe was contemporary with Shakespeare. 马洛与莎士比亚是同时代的。 2. He had devoted his whole life to the study of contemporary art. 他把他的一生都献给了当代艺术研究。 3. Thackeray is a contemporary of Dickens. 萨克莱跟狄更斯是同时期的人。 4. She and I were contemporaries at college. 她和我在学院里是同学。', '副词: contemporarily 名词复数: contemporaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('staggering', '[\'stæɡərɪŋ]', 'adj.摇晃的；惊人的 动词stagger的现在分词.', '1. The amounts involved are staggering, Rogers said. 所涉及的金额是惊人的，罗杰斯说。 2. The Asian countries are getting westernized at a staggering rate. 亚洲国家正以惊人的速度变得西方化。', '副词: staggeringly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shallow', '[\'ʃæloʊ]', 'adj.浅的；薄的 n.浅滩；浅处 v.变浅', '1. This shallow ford made it possible for us to cross the river. 我们有可能从这片浅滩过河。 2. That dish is too shallow to serve soup in. 那只盘子太浅了，不能盛汤。 3. Homesickness is a shallow strait, I stand here, my homeland is on the other side. 乡愁是一湾浅浅的海峡,我在这头,大陆在那头。 4. She has a rather shallow personality. 她的个性相当浅薄。 5. This shallow ford made it possible for us to cross the river. 我们有可能从这片浅滩过河。 6. The rock assemblage of shallow exposed bank-microfacies is the basis of the formation of pore layers and reservoir permeability systems. 变浅暴露滩微相的岩石组合是孔隙层和储渗体形成的基础。', '副词: shallowly 比较级: shallower 最高级: shallowest 名词: shallowness 过去式: shallowed 过去分词: shallowed 现在分词: shallowing 第三人称单数: shallows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('garnish', '[\'ɡɑːrnɪʃ]', 'n.装饰；装饰品；勒索金 v.装饰；配菜；[法]传讯', '1. The turkey was served with a garnish of parsley. 做好的火鸡上面配上芫荽菜做点缀。 2. I\'d rather you didn\'t serve the dish with a garnish. 我希望菜上面没有什么点缀。 3. They garnish the room with modern painting. 他们以现代画装饰此房间。 4. Garnish the fish with cucumber slices. 这个鱼就用黄瓜片作配菜。', '过去式: garnished 过去分词: garnished 现在分词: garnishing 第三人称单数: garnishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complement', '[\'kɑːmplɪment]', 'vt.相辅相成 n.补足物；补语；余角', '1. This wine complements the food perfectly. 用这种酒配这种菜肴最妙不过了。 2. His business skill complements her flair for design. 他的经营技巧和她的设计才能相辅相成。 3. A wine is a complement to a good meal. 美食加美酒才算完备。 4. In the sentence \'I\'m angry\', \'angry\' is the complement. 在I\'m angry一句中,angry是补语。', '过去式: complemented 过去分词: complemented 现在分词: complementing 第三人称单数: complements');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('riot', '[\'raɪət]', 'n.暴乱；骚乱；喧闹；（色彩）丰富；<俚>有趣的人 v.闹事；骚乱', '1. The military were called in to deal with the riot. 已将军队调来镇压暴乱。 2. The outbreak of riot caused many people to die. 暴乱的发生使很多人丧生。 3. The police stopped several riots on election night. 警方在竞选之夜制止了几处骚乱。 4. Football hooligans ran riot through the town. 闹事的足球迷在城里胡作非为。 5. He fermented prejudiced crowds to riot. 他煽动有偏见的群众起来闹事。', '名词: rioter 过去式: rioted 过去分词: rioted 现在分词: rioting 第三人称单数: riots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('octopus', '[\'ɑːktəpəs]', 'n.章鱼', '1. One octopus has eight tentacles. 一条章鱼有八根触角。 2. Who can know the woe of my octopus. 谁能知道我章鱼的悲哀。', '名词复数: octopuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subdue', '[səb\'duː]', 'v.使服从；压制；减弱', '1. No one has been able to subdue these areas. 从没有人能够压制这一地区。 2. Soames made a tour of the room, to subdue his rising anger. 索米斯在屋内兜了一圈，压制一下心头升起的怒火。', '形容词: subduable 名词: subduer 过去式: subdued 过去分词: subdued 现在分词: subduing 第三人称单数: subdues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('handicap', '[\'hændikæp]', 'n.障碍 vt.妨碍', '1. Blindness is a great handicap. 失明是极大的障碍。 2. Deafness can be a serious handicap. 耳聋算是严重的缺陷。 3. Poor eyesight is a handicap to a student. 视力不好对学生来说是一个障碍。 4. It takes a lot of grit to overcome a physical handicap. 要很大的毅力来克服生理上的障碍。 5. Ignorance can handicap the progress of a city. 无知会妨碍城市的进步。', '过去式: handicapped 过去分词: handicapped 现在分词: handicapping 第三人称单数: handicaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('replicate', '[\'replɪkeɪt]', 'v.复制；模拟；折叠 n.复制品 adj.复制的；折叠的', '1. It is a business decision to determine exactly what kind of data to replicate. 准确确定要复制的数据类型是一项商业决定。 2. Viruses usually replicate at the primary site of the entry. 病毒通常在侵入的位置复制。 3. Researchers tried many times to replicate the original experiment. 研究人员尝试了很多次来模拟最初的实验。 4. It is a business decision to determine exactly what kind of data to replicate. 准确确定要复制的数据类型是一项商业决定。', '形容词: replicative 过去式: replicated 过去分词: replicated 现在分词: replicating 第三人称单数: replicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('astonished', '[ə\'stɑːnɪʃt]', 'adj.惊讶的 动词astonish的过去式和过去分词.', '1. I was astonished at the news. 这消息着实让我吃了一惊。 2. His wife was astonished at the astronomical sum of money he had spent. 他的妻子被他花的天文数字的钱款惊呆了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pressure', '[\'preʃər]', 'n.压强；压力；压迫 v.施压', '1. My father suffers from high blood pressure. 我父亲有高血压。 2. The pressure of work was too great for him. 工作的压力使他承受不了。 3. He works well under pressure. 他在有压力的情况下工作很出色。 4. The tooth became sore to pressure and there is a dull gnawing pain. 该齿对于压迫作痛，且有钝麻如咬的疼痛。 5. Now you are trying to pressure me. 你现在试图向我施压。', '过去式: pressured 过去分词: pressured 现在分词: pressuring 第三人称单数: pressures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enlighten', '[ɪn\'laɪtn]', 'v.启发；开导；教导', '1. This book will enlighten the reader. 这本书将会启发读者。 2. Enlighten me with your thoughts on this matter. 你们在如下事件上的思想启发了我。 3. Can you enlighten me--I don\'t understand this proposal. 我不明白这条建议，你能不能启发我一下。 4. Can you enlighten me on this subject? 关于这个问题，你能指点我一下吗？', '名词: enlightener 过去式: enlightened 过去分词: enlightened 现在分词: enlightening 第三人称单数: enlightens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nurture', '[\'nɜːrtʃər]', 'vt.养育；培育；照顾；扶持 n.养育；培育；环境因素', '1. She nurtured the child as if he had been her own. 她把那个孩子当作自己的孩子来教育。 2. Most vegetables we buy in winter are nurtured in the greenhouse. 我们冬天买的大多数蔬菜都是在温室里培育的。 3. We have to care for and nurture the plant first. 我们必须先要照顾灌溉树木。 4. They are best friends and nurture each other. 他们是最好的朋友，并且相互扶持。 5. The child got his nurture from his loving parents. 这个孩子的教育来自他慈爱的双亲。', '名词: nurturer 过去式: nurtured 过去分词: nurtured 现在分词: nurturing 第三人称单数: nurtures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('retort', '[rɪ\'tɔːrt]', 'v.反驳；回嘴；反击 n.反驳；顶嘴', '1. He retorted that it was my fault as much as his. 他反驳说我的错误并不比他的小。 2. The analysts could retort only that the geometric proofs were clumsy and inelegant. 分析学家只能回嘴说几何的证明是笨拙而不优美的。 3. \'Don\'t be ridiculous!\' Pat retorted angrily. “别荒唐了！”帕特生气地回答道。 4. Her roommate\'s retort made her angry. 她同屋的反驳使她生气。', '名词: retorter 过去式: retorted 过去分词: retorted 现在分词: retorting 第三人称单数: retorts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perfect', '[\'pɜːrfɪkt]', 'adj.完美的；完全的；完满的；十足的；理想的 vt.使完美；使完全', '1. Laurel was a perfect girl in every way. 从各方面讲，罗拉都是一个完美的女孩。 2. No one expects you to be perfect, but we do expect you to do your best always. 没人指望你完美无缺，但是我们盼望你永远尽最大的努力。 3. One day being perfect health is much. 获得一天完全的健康也不算少。 4. I insist on perfect sobriety and silence. 我坚决要求完全的肃静。 5. She went to France to perfect her French. 她为了学好法语去过法国。', '名词: perfecter 过去式: perfected 过去分词: perfected 现在分词: perfecting 第三人称单数: perfects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chlorine', '[\'klɔːriːn]', 'n.氯', '1. All the chlorine atoms have already found partners. 所有的氯原子都已找到了配对的伙伴。 2. Common salt is a compound of sodium and chlorine. 食盐是钠和氯的化合物。', '简写符号: Cl');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evoke', '[ɪ\'voʊk]', 'vt.唤起；引起', '1. Songs can evoke old memories. 歌曲可以唤起往日的回忆。 2. Pieces of fine art may evoke emotional or spiritual responses in us. 一件件精美的艺术品可以唤起我们情感和精神上的响应。 3. The photographs evoked strong memories of our holidays in France. 照片唤起了我们在法国度假的深深的记忆。 4. His case is unlikely to evoke public sympathy. 他的情况不大可能引起公众的同情。', '形容词: evocable 过去式: evoked 过去分词: evoked 现在分词: evoking 第三人称单数: evokes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('underneath', '[ˌʌndər\'niːθ]', 'adv.在下面 n.下部；底部 prep.在 ... 下面', '1. She was wearing a woolen coat, with a cotton blouse underneath. 她外面穿了一件毛外套，里面穿一件棉布衬衫。 2. Put a bowl underneath to catch the overflow. 把盆放在下面接住溢出物。 3. The glacier is constantly shifting underneath. 冰川在下面持续的移动。 4. The underneath part felt damp. 底层很潮湿。 5. She found a lot of dust underneath the carpet. 她发觉地毯下面有许多尘土.', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recruit', '[rɪ\'kruːt]', 'v.吸收(新成员)；征兵；招聘 n.新成员；新兵', '1. We are having difficulties in recruiting well-qualified staff. 我们难以招募到素质好的职员。 2. His job was to recruit for the army. 他的工作是为陆军募兵。 3. We lower the standards in order to recruit real talents. 我们降低标准是为了招纳真正的人才。 4. This job presents many difficulties to the new recruit. 这件工作对那个新手来说困难重重。', '名词: recruiter 过去式: recruited 过去分词: recruited 现在分词: recruiting 第三人称单数: recruits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diminish', '[dɪ\'mɪnɪʃ]', 'vt.减少；减损；贬低 vi.变少；逐渐变细', '1. We should try to diminish the cost of production. 我们应尽力减少生产成本。 2. His illness diminished his health. 疾病侵蚀了他的健康。 3. He likes to diminish the skills of others. 他喜欢贬低别人的技能。 4. The amount of water in the pond will diminish as the dry season continues. 如果旱季还持续下去，池塘中的水量将减少。', '形容词: diminishable 名词: diminishment 过去式: diminished 过去分词: diminished 现在分词: diminishing 第三人称单数: diminishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('texture', '[\'tekstʃər]', 'n.质地；手感；口感；组织；结构；纹理；特点 vt.给予结构', '1. This kind of cloth has a close texture. 这种布质地很紧密。 2. We could feel the smooth texture of silk. 我们能感觉出丝绸的光滑质地。 3. The texture of the rug was very soft. 毯子的手感非常柔软。 4. The cake has a nice light texture. 这蛋糕松软可口。', '形容词: textural 副词: texturally 过去式: textured 过去分词: textured 现在分词: texturing 第三人称单数: textures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('estimable', '[\'estɪməbl]', 'adj.〈旧或文〉值得尊敬的；可估计的', '1. Firstly, under the condition that the nonlinear dynamic function of the systems is estimable and bounded, sliding mode control law is presented. 首先，在系统的非线性动态函数满足可估计和有界两个基本假设的条件下，给出了此类系统基于非线性动态函数估计的一般滑模控制律设计。', '副词: estimably 名词: estimableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lusty', '[\'lʌsti]', 'adj.健壮的；精力充沛的；贪欲的；欢乐的', '1. He has a strong and lusty son. 他有一个体格健壮精力充沛的儿子。 2. On the benches in his shop were the lusty and valiant young men. 他店内凳子上坐的都是一些强壮骠悍的小伙子。 3. A lusty lady loved a lawyer and longed to lure him from his laboratory. 一位妖媚的小姐爱上了一个律师，渴望能诱使他远离他的实验室。 4. Mary is a lusty singer and a devastating take-off artist. 玛丽是一个活泼的歌唱演员，也是一个极善挖苦模仿别人的人。', '副词: lustily 比较级: lustier 最高级: lustiest 名词: lustiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perspective', '[pər\'spektɪv]', 'n.远景；看法；透视 adj.透视的', '1. A fine perspective opened out before us. 一幅美丽的远景展开在我们眼前。 2. Do you agree with this perspective? 你同意这个看法吗? 3. The painting provides us with one of the earliest examples of the use of perspective. 那幅画给我们提供了采用透视画法的最早的范例。 4. The first row of each perspective shows its name. 每个透视的第一行都显示该透视的名称。', '形容词: perspectival 副词: perspectively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wry', '[raɪ]', 'adj.面部肌肉扭曲的；啼笑皆非的；讽刺的', '1. Gradually a wry smile settled on his face. 一丝苦笑浮现在他脸上。 2. He acknowledged his mistake with a wry grimace. 他做了个怪怪的表情，算是认了错。 3. This is a wry comedy about family life. 这是一部关于家庭生活的讽刺喜剧。', '副词: wryly 比较级: wrier/wryer 最高级: wriest/wryest 名词: wryness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('betray', '[bɪ\'treɪ]', 'vt.背叛；出卖；泄露；显露', '1. He betrayed his country. 他背叛了他的国家。 2. He promised never to betray the organization. 他发誓永不背叛组织。 3. He was seduced to betray his friend. 他受唆使而出卖朋友。 4. As long as you don\'t betray me, I\'ll do whatever you ask me to. 只要你不出卖我,要我做什么我都愿意。', '名词: betrayal 过去式: betrayed 过去分词: betrayed 现在分词: betraying 第三人称单数: betrays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adolescence', '[ˌædə\'lesns]', 'n.青春期（一般指13～16岁的发育期）', '1. Adolescence is no time to be lulled to sleep. 青春期不是让人哄着入睡的时候了。 2. Can excessive masturbation affect adolescence long? 青春期过度手淫会影响长个吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gibe', '[dʒaɪb]', 'v.嘲笑；讥笑 n.嘲笑；嘲讽话 =jibe.', '1. It\'s impolite to gibe at a foreign student\'s English. 嘲笑外国学生的英语是不礼貌的。 2. The gibe smarted in his brain. 人家的嘲笑令他脑子针扎似地作痛。 3. If we substitute the idea of respect for the audience, the gibe is turned against the player. 如果我们除去这个意思，放进尊重对象的意思去，那就只剩下讥笑弹琴者这个意思了。 4. It\'s impolite to gibe at a foreign student\'s English. 嘲笑外国学生的英语是不礼貌的。', '副词: gibingly 名词: giber');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('watch', '[wɑːtʃ]', 'v.注视；看守；观看 n.手表；监视；看守；值班', '1. I seldom play chess, but I like to watch. 我很少下棋，但是喜欢看。 2. Watch what I do and how I do it. 注意看我的动作和方法。 3. I was assigned to watch the road. 我被派去护路。 4. We sat there watching basketball. 我们坐在那看篮球比赛。 5. How much is that watch? 那块手表多少钱?', '过去式: watched 过去分词: watched 现在分词: watching 第三人称单数: watches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appointment', '[ə\'pɔɪntmənt]', 'n.约会；任命；设备；职位', '1. I\'ve made an appointment for a facial next week. 我已经预约了下周去美容。 2. He wants to change his appointment from Monday to Wednesday. 他想把他的约会从星期一改到星期三。 3. His promotion to manager was a popular appointment. 他升任经理是众望所归的。 4. The appointments in this hotel are very good. 这旅馆的设备很好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('connive', '[kə\'naɪv]', 'v.共谋；默许；纵容', '1. We want to let to benefit the customer and connive development. 我们就是要做到让利于客户 2. The student tried to connive with her friend to cheat in the examination. 那个学生企图和她的朋友串谋考试作弊。 3. Some government officials connive at graft. 有些政府官员对贪污受贿视而不见。 4. The prisoners paid the guards to connive at their escape. 囚犯们贿赂看守，使看守默许他们越狱。', '名词: conniver 过去式: connived 过去分词: connived 现在分词: conniving 第三人称单数: connives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dispute', '[dɪ\'spjuːt]', 'v.争论；辩驳；争议；质疑 n.争论；争端；争吵', '1. The couple disputed where to spend the holiday. 夫妻俩为上哪儿度假而发生争论。 2. It is ridiculous to dispute about such a thing. 为这样的事情而争论简直荒谬可笑。 3. \"I\'m not disputing what you say, matt.\" said Tremaine, shaking his head. “我并不是要跟你辩驳，麦特”，屈里曼说，摇摇头。 4. Now there was just one point on the boundary left to dispute. 边界上有一点引起争议。 5. A long dispute means that both parties are wrong.( Voltaire) 持久的争论意味着双方都是错的。(伏尔泰)', '名词: disputer 过去式: disputed 过去分词: disputed 现在分词: disputing 第三人称单数: disputes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abolition', '[ˌæbə\'lɪʃn]', 'n.废除；废止', '1. He long urged the abolition of capital punishment. 他长期要求废除死刑。 2. It has been two years since the abolition of the custom. 这种习俗已经废止两年了。 3. The abolition of foreign stereotypes was demanded in that report, yet some comrades are still promoting them. 这里叫洋八股废止，有些同志却实际上还在提倡。', '形容词: abolitionary');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('romantic', '[roʊ\'mæntɪk]', 'adj.浪漫的；不切实际的 n.浪漫的人', '1. I was told that Spain is a romantic nation. 有人告诉我说，西班牙是个浪漫的国家。 2. It is said that Frenchmen are among the most romantic people in the world. 据说法国人是世界上最浪漫的民族之一。 3. His head is stuffed with silly romantic ideas. 他满脑子天真的想法。 4. She has romantic notions about becoming a famous actress. 她心里充满幻想，总希望有一天会成为著名演员。 5. Romantic is the last thing I am. 我是最不浪漫的人。', '副词: romantically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deteriorate', '[dɪ\'tɪriəreɪt]', 'v.恶化；变质；衰退', '1. We cannot allow the situation to deteriorate. 我们不容许情况恶化。 2. Relation between the two countries have deteriorated sharply in recent week. 最近几周那两个国家间的关系严重恶化了。 3. Food is apt to deteriorate in summer. 食物在夏天容易变质。 4. The discussion deteriorated into a bitter quarrel. 这场讨论演变成了激烈的争吵。', '形容词: deteriorative 名词: deterioration 过去式: deteriorated 过去分词: deteriorated 现在分词: deteriorating 第三人称单数: deteriorates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grading', '[\'ɡreɪdɪŋ]', 'n.等级；分阶段；坡度缓和 动词grade的现在分词.', '1. This grading of wool can be sold at a fairly low price. 这种等级的羊毛只能以相当低的价格卖出。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fade', '[feɪd]', 'v.逐渐消失；褪色；凋谢 n.淡入；淡出', '1. Hopes of a peaceful settlement are now fading. 和平解决的希望正在消失。 2. The closing music fades out when the hero rides off into the sunset. 当男主角策马向夕阳驰去时，尾声音乐逐渐消失。 3. As evening came the coastline faded into darkness. 夜晚来临，海岸线融入茫茫夜色中。 4. These sunproof curtains will not fade . 这些耐晒的窗帘不褪色。 5. They\'ll fade in to an outdoor scene. 他们将淡入至户外的一个场景。', '过去式: faded 过去分词: faded 现在分词: fading 第三人称单数: fades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inquiry', '[ɪn\'kwaɪrɪ]', 'n.调查；询问；打听；查问 =enquiry(英).', '1. We made an application to the court for an inquiry. 我们曾请求法院调查。 2. They\'ve promised a thorough inquiry into the plane crash. 他们答应对这次飞机失事进行彻底的调查。 3. I\'m not able to help you with your inquiry. 我对你的咨询无能为力。 4. He is fishing for information by a letter of inquiry. 他写信询问，希望打听一下消息。', '异体字: enquiry 名词复数: inquiries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dismay', '[dɪs\'meɪ]', 'n.沮丧；绝望 vt.使 ... 沮丧；使 ... 惊愕', '1. The enemy retreated in perfect dismay. 敌人沮丧地退去。 2. To my dismay, he made the same mistakes. 让我感到沮丧的是，他又犯了同样的错误。 3. He watched the burning bouse with dismay. 他绝望地看着着火的房子。 4. The teacher was dismayed at the students\' lack of response. 老师对学生的毫无反应感到沮丧。', '副词: dismayingly 过去式: dismayed 过去分词: dismayed 现在分词: dismaying 第三人称单数: dismays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hygiene', '[\'haɪdʒiːn]', 'n.卫生；卫生学', '1. People should wash regularly to ensure personal hygiene. 人们应经常洗澡以保证个人卫生。 2. Many diseases proceed from negligence of hygiene. 许多疾病源于不讲卫生。 3. He\'s going to give us a lecture on public hygiene. 他要给我们作关于公共卫生方面的报告。 4. Hygiene has evolved into preventive medicine. 卫生学已逐步发展成为预防医学。', '名词: hygienist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('collectively', '[kə\'lektɪvli]', 'adv.共同地；集体地；总体地', '1. Complex, critical choices will have to be made by human beings individually and collectively. 人类将不得不个别地或共同地做出复杂而关键的选择。 2. Collectively, the Honeywell solutions will serve to streamline the production line, helping to increase output and enhance product quality. 共同地，霍尼韦尔的解决方案将服务于产品生产线，帮助提高产量加强产品质量。 3. As one species, humanity learns collectively through both the individual experiences and spiritual lessons learned, and the collective lessons learned and understood. 作为一个物种，人类集体地通过个人经验和灵性课程所得的来学习，然后集体的课程就被学到和理解。 4. Under the guidance of the Tao, we are moving towards a new level of music individually and collectively that restores a state of internal peace and love. 在道的引导之下，我们正在个体与集体地，走向一种恢复了内在和平与爱状态的新层次音乐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lounge', '[laʊndʒ]', 'n.休息室；候机室；起居室 v.闲荡；懒散地斜靠', '1. We watched television in the hotel lounge. 我们在旅馆休息室里看电视。 2. Please move forward to the passenger lounge . 请向前走到旅客休息室。 3. She is waiting for me in the departure lounge. 她在候机室等我。 4. The children have made an awful mess in the lounge. 孩子们把起居室弄得凌乱不堪。 5. I don\'t want to lounge about town. I have other things to do. 我不想在市区闲逛。我还有别的事要做。', '名词: lounger 过去式: lounged 过去分词: lounged 现在分词: lounging 第三人称单数: lounges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concede', '[kən\'siːd]', 'vt.承认；给予；让步；认输 vi.让步', '1. I concede that you are right. 我承认你是对的。 2. You must concede that I have tried my best. 你必须承认我已经尽力了。 3. The defeated side had to concede some of their territory to the enemy. 战败的一方不得不把一部分领土割让给了敌人。 4. You concede nothing to me and I have to concede everything to you. 你对我无论什么都不肯让步；我对你，可无论什么都得让步。 5. Mike had to concede when he confronted his parents 当面对他的父母,麦克不得不让步。', '副词: concededly 名词: conceder 过去式: conceded 过去分词: conceded 现在分词: conceding 第三人称单数: concedes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unaided', '[ʌn\'eɪdɪd]', 'adj.未受协助的；独立的', '1. That comet is invisible to the unaided eye. 那颗彗星只用肉眼是看不到的。 2. No one gets to be a human being unaided. 没有一个人类是不需要帮助的。 3. Four months to the day, Ralph finally stood unaided. 到今天就四个月了，拉尔夫终于独立地站立起来。 4. The baby cannot sit unaided and she has to be propped up on pillows. 那婴儿还不会坐', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('surrender', '[sə\'rendər]', 'v.投降；屈服；放弃 n.投降；屈服；放弃', '1. It was shameful of them to surrender. 他们投降是可耻的。 2. We would rather die than surrender. 我们宁死而不投降。 3. They surrendered to the enemy. 他们向敌人投降了。 4. We can never surrender to him. 而我们绝对不能够屈服。 5. The garrison was starved into surrender. 卫戍部队因遭到断粮而投降。', '过去式: surrendered 过去分词: surrendered 现在分词: surrendering 第三人称单数: surrenders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nomadic', '[nəʊ\'mædɪk]', 'adj.游牧的；游牧民族的；流浪的', '1. His tribe was unusual for its sedentarism.Plains tribes were commonly nomadic. 他的部落过着与众不同的隐居生活，而平原上的部落一般都是游牧的。 2. The Ming adopted a new strategy to keep the nomadic Mongols out by constructing walls along the northern border of China. 明朝采取了一个新的策略通过沿中国北方边界建造长城来阻挡游牧的蒙古。 3. I don\'t have known nomadic blood in the family. 据我所知，我身上并没有游牧民族的血液。 4. The Yuma Indians, such as this tribesman, were generally nomadic. 照片中的部落男人就是尤马族的印第安人，他们通常都是游牧民族。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('settlement', '[\'setlmənt]', 'n.解决；结算；协议；安置；殖民；定居', '1. There is no prospect of a settlement of the dispute. 这场纠纷根本不可能获得解决。 2. Negotiators are looking for a peaceful settlement to the dispute. 谈判双方正寻求和平解决争端的办法。 3. After much discussion the negotiators hammered out a compromise settlement. 双方经多次谈判达成一项折衷的解决办法。 4. I enclose a cheque in settlement of your account. 兹附支票一张以结清贵处帐目。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('luminous', '[\'luːmɪnəs]', 'adj.发光的；发亮的；清楚的；明白易懂的', '1. These reactions are not luminous. 这些反应是不发光的。 2. They like the luminous stones like diamonds in our reality. 他们喜欢发光的石头像现实中的钻石。 3. With this watch you can tell time in the dark because its hands and dial are luminous. 用这只表你可以在黑暗中看时间，因为它的针和针盘都是会发亮的。 4. We are part of eternity, a tremendously luminous experience of ecstasy that is beyond words. 我们是永恒的一部分，有一个极其巨大的发亮的狂喜体验很难用语言表达。', '副词: luminously 名词: luminousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evacuation', '[ɪˌvækju\'eɪʃn]', 'n.撤离；疏散 n.排泄；排泄物', '1. This decrease and the cold weather complicated evacuation work. 这种减少以及寒冷的气候使撤离的工作更加复杂化。 2. Orders went out to prepare for the evacuation of the city. 为撤离该城作准备的命令已下达。 3. Police and firemen continued to hasten evacuation of the hotel. 警察和消防队员继续加快疏散饭店的工作。 4. An increase in foreshock activity triggered the evacuation warning. 前震活动的增加引发了疏散警报。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mutation', '[mjuː\'teɪʃn]', 'n.变化；突变；变异', '1. Our teacher has mutation of sounds suddenly. 我们的老师突然语音发生了变化。 2. A change, or mutation, happens when the order of the letters changes. 当这些字母的排列顺序有所变化时，就会发生基因突变。 3. People who have this mutation need less sleep than others. 有这种突变的人需要的睡眠比其他人少。 4. The mutations in plants caused by radiation have been found in experiments. 放射线引起植物变异已在实验中被证实。', '形容词: mutational 副词: mutationally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fermentation', '[ˌfɜːmen\'teɪʃn]', 'n.发酵；骚动', '1. Fermentation is a biogenic process. 发酵是一种生物化学反应过程。 2. Sparkling wine needs to undergo a second alcoholic fermentation. 发泡葡萄酒需要二次发酵作用。 3. He shared the 1929 Nobel Prize for research on the fermentation of sugars. 他因在糖发酵上的研究和别人同获1929年的诺贝尔奖。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pacify', '[\'pæsɪfaɪ]', 'v.使 ... 平静；抚慰；安慰', '1. She knew that he had become delirious, and tried to pacify him. 她知道他已经神志昏迷起来了，极力想使他镇静下来。 2. He tried to pacify the protesters with promise of reform. 他试图以改革的承诺安抚抗议者。 3. I bought an ice cream to pacify my crying daughter. 我买了个冰淇淋来抚慰哭泣的女儿。', '形容词: pacifiable 过去式: pacified 过去分词: pacified 现在分词: pacifying 第三人称单数: pacifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('obtain', '[əb\'teɪn]', 'vt.获得；得到 vi.流行；通用；存在', '1. He failed to obtain a scholarship. 他没有获得奖学金。 2. At last, their company obtained the mining concession. 他们的公司最终获得了采矿权。 3. Those who were penitent obtained absolution. 悔过者获得了赦免。 4. They obtained a loan from the government. 他们从政府那里得到一笔贷款。 5. Your dress still obtains now. 你的这款套裙现在还很流行。', '形容词: obtainable 名词: obtainer 过去式: obtained 过去分词: obtained 现在分词: obtaining 第三人称单数: obtains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gear', '[ɡɪr]', 'n.传动装置；齿轮；排挡；工具；装备 v.调整；使适应于；以齿轮连起', '1. Careless use of the clutch may damage the gears. 离合器使用不慎可能损坏传动装置。 2. The gear just would not come unstuck. 齿轮就是松不开来。 3. The car has four forward gear and one reverse gear. 那汽车有四个前进挡和一个倒挡。 4. Lifting electromagnet is a kind of lifting gear. 起重电磁铁是起重工具的一种。 5. Education should be geared to the children\'s needs and abilities. 教育应适应儿童的需要和能力。', '过去式: geared 过去分词: geared 现在分词: gearing 第三人称单数: gears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('catalog', '[\'kætəlɔːg]', 'n.目录；大学概况手册；商品型录 vt.做目录；分类说明；名入列表 vi.(商品)在型录中明码标价', '1. You can look for the book in the library catalog. 你可以在图书馆的图书目录上查找这本书。 2. These names are to be listed in the catalog. 这些名字将列入目录。 3. Please show me a catalog of your books. 请拿一本图书目录给我看看。 4. Has the Harvard catalog come yet? 哈佛大学简介来了吗？ 5. Can you catalog all these books? 你能给所有这些书编目录吗？ 6. This stamp catalogues at two dollars. 这张邮票的目录价格为2美元。', '异体字: catalogue 名词: cataloger 过去式: cataloged/catalogued 过去分词: cataloged/catalogued 现在分词: cataloging/cataloguing 第三人称单数: catalogs/catalogues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dwelling', '[\'dwelɪŋ]', 'n.住处；住宅', '1. He changed his dwelling recently. 他最近搬了家。 2. The smoke betrays where the dwelling lies. 炊烟起处有人家。 3. Our stable abuts against his dwelling. 我们的马厩和他的住所毗连。 4. We weathered out the winter in a lonely dwelling. 我们在一所偏僻的房子里熬过了冬天。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foe', '[foʊ]', 'n.敌人；仇敌', '1. The knight was murdered by his foes. 那位骑士被他的敌人谋杀了。 2. A courageous foe is better than a cowardly friend. 勇敢的敌人胜过懦怯的朋友。 3. She was unsure as yet whether he was friend or foe. 她还不确定他究竟是敌是友。 4. They were all humbled by kobe who is their foe. 视他为仇敌的对手在他面前依旧得低头。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avid', '[\'ævɪd]', 'adj.渴望的；贪婪的；热心的', '1. Avid fans of the show attribute the loss of ratings to a misjudgement on the part of FOX Network for airing the second season on Friday evenings instead of Tuesday evenings. 渴望的影迷把低收视率归咎于富克斯网络的判断不公，把放映时间从星期二改为星期五晚。 2. She was also an avid photographer. 亚非还是个热心的摄影家。 3. I cajoled the avid entrepreneur into doing the business for me. 我引诱那个热心的企业家为我做生意。', '副词: avidly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slog', '[slɑːɡ]', 'v.艰难行进；猛击；苦干；决出胜负 n.苦工；长途跋涉', '1. He started to slog his way through the undergrowth. 他踏上了穿越林莽的艰难征程。 2. I slog my guts out and get paid only a hundred pounds a week. 我工作非常努力，但每星期只有100英镑的报酬。 3. The two teams will slog it out for second place. 这两个队将争夺第二名。 4. The party leader be slog it out in a Tv debate. 政党领袖在电视辩论中一决雌雄。 5. Marking the exam papers was quite a slog. 评阅试卷是很辛苦的工作。', '名词: slogger 过去式: slogged 过去分词: slogged 现在分词: slogging 第三人称单数: slogs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exclusive', '[ɪk\'skluːsɪv]', 'adj.排外的；独占的；唯一的；完整的；奢华的 n.独家新闻；独权', '1. He is part of an exclusive social circle and belongs to an exclusive club. 他所处的社交圈子很排外，而且参加的又是个很排外的社团。 2. The interview is exclusive to this magazine. 本杂志得到独家访问权。 3. Painting has not been her exclusive occupation. 绘画并非她唯一的职业. 4. The teacher tried to gain the students\' exclusive attention. 老师努力试着获得学生的全部注意力。 5. Everyone was surprised by the Times exclusive about the prince\' marriage. 泰晤士报关于王子大婚的独家新闻令很多人惊奇不已。', '副词: exclusively 名词: exclusiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ultimately', '[\'ʌltɪmətli]', 'adv.最后；最终', '1. Every value they created ultimately redounded to his boss. 他们创造的价值最后全进了他们老板的腰包。 2. Ultimately, the success of the product depends on the good marketing. 最终，产品的成功还是取决于高明的销售手段。 3. His rashness led ultimately to his ruin. 他的急躁鲁莽最终导致了他的毁灭。 4. The committee ultimately adopted his suggestions. 委员会最终采纳了他的建议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flout', '[flaʊt]', 'v.藐视；轻视；嘲笑 n.嘲弄；轻视', '1. No one can flout the law with impunity. 任何人都不能不受惩罚地藐视法律。 2. They flouted all our offers of help and friendship. 他们对我们愿意提供的所有帮助和友谊表示藐视。 3. The foolish boy flout his mother\'s advice. 这个愚蠢的孩子轻视他母亲的劝告。', '副词: floutingly 名词: flouter 过去式: flouted 过去分词: flouted 现在分词: flouting 第三人称单数: flouts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('buck', '[bʌk]', 'n.<俚>一美元 n.钱；雄鹿；雄兔；(鹿皮等)制物；<美口>年轻男子 v.马弓背踢后腿挑起；抵制；振作', '1. People want to make a quick buck. 人人都想赚容易钱。 2. The buck shook his antlers ferociously. 那雄鹿猛烈地摇动他的鹿角。 3. The buck jumped into the woods before the hunter raised his gun. 还没等猎人举起枪来那只雄鹿就跳进了树林。 4. Both buck and doe have a little gait and both their eyelids palpitate. 雄兔脚扑朔，雌兔眼迷离。 5. The horse may still buck, but now the peeler can start topping it off. 虽然那匹马还会猛然弯背跃起，但现在驯马者可以结束对它的驯服工作了。', '名词: bucker 过去式: bucked 过去分词: bucked 现在分词: bucking 第三人称单数: bucks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('harbor', '[\'hɑːbə]', 'n.海港；避难所 vt.庇护；心怀；窝藏 vi.生存；进入避祸所', '1. The ship steamed into the harbor. 船驶入了港湾。 2. The bombers made a sudden strike on the harbor. 轰炸机对这港口进行了一次突然袭击。 3. They also harbor exotic life-forms, far below the reach of sunlight. 他们也是外来的生物避难所，远远低于阳光的到达。 4. They harbored refugees in times of war. 他们在战争期间收留难民。 5. The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life. 据我们所知,地球是唯一维持生物生存的世界。', '名词: harborer 过去式: harbored 过去分词: harbored 现在分词: harboring 第三人称单数: harbors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('patriot', '[\'peɪtriət]', 'n.爱国者', '1. The patriot sticks to his moral principles. 那个爱国者固守他自已的道德信念。 2. He regards himself as a patriot. 他自认为是个爱国者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scarf', '[skɑːrf]', 'n.围巾', '1. The price of this scarf is below ten dollars. 这条围巾价格不到10美元。 2. She twisted the long scarf round her head. 她把那条长围巾围在头上。 3. She threw a scarf over her shoulders. 她在肩上披上一块肩巾。', '名词: scarfer 名词复数: scarves 过去式: scarfed 过去分词: scarfed 现在分词: scarfing 第三人称单数: scarfs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('renowned', '[rɪ\'naʊnd]', 'adj.有名的；有声誉的', '1. The Emperor is a renowned patron of learning. 这位皇帝是一位有名的崇尚学术的君王。 2. I\'ve invited a renowned calligrapher to write an inscription for my restaurant. 我请了一位有名的书法家为我的饭店题额。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transit', '[\'trænzɪt]', 'n.运输；经过；转变；[天]中天；凌日；经纬仪 vt.穿越；旋转 vi.越过', '1. The goods were lost in transit. 这些货物在运输中丢失了。 2. The transit was damaged by flood. 运输线被洪水破坏了。 3. Firstly, the drug inhibits octopamine transit in insect brains. 第一，可卡因能抑制真蛸胺这种药物在昆虫大脑中经过。 4. The city supported an initiative to turn this space, a place of transit, into an actual facility with a more permanent character and a new urban identity and artistic spirit. 该城市支持了一项倡议，把这个空间里转变成为一个实际的设施，且与更长期的和新的城市特征及艺术气息相融合。 5. We will transit the strait at night. 我们将在夜间通过那个海峡。 6. Our ship used the canal to transit to the east. 我们的船通过这条运河驶往东方。', '过去式: transited 过去分词: transited 现在分词: transiting 第三人称单数: transits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devout', '[dɪ\'vaʊt]', 'adj.虔诚的；虔敬的；衷心的', '1. The devout Christian persists in his belief. 那个虔诚的基督教徒坚持他的信念。 2. Devout Moslems oBserve Ramadan punctiliously. 虔诚的穆斯林准时地遵守斋月。', '副词: devoutly 比较级: devouter 最高级: devoutest 名词: devoutness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squid', '[skwɪd]', 'n.鱿鱼', '1. Try to get your fishmonger to skin and gut the squid for you. 让鱼贩子帮你收拾一下鱿鱼，去皮和内脏。 2. They also eat animal cephalopods, including squid and octopus. 它们还吃头足纲动物，包括鱿鱼和章鱼。', '名词复数: squids');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cascade', '[kæ\'skeɪd]', 'n.瀑布；[电]串联 v.瀑布似地落下；（将 ... ）连结；串联', '1. The water formed a cascade down the mountain. 水沿山泻下，形成一条瀑布。 2. Climbing plants with their bright flowers hung in cascades over the garden wall. 开出鲜艳花朵的爬藤植物瀑布般悬挂在花园墙上。 3. When it rained, water would cascade down the window. 下雨的时候，雨水像瀑布一样沿着窗沿泻下。 4. We can cascade them to determine their overall effect. 我们可以将它们串联起来确定它们的总体影响。', '过去式: cascaded 过去分词: cascaded 现在分词: cascading 第三人称单数: cascades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lottery', '[\'lɑːtəri]', 'n.彩票', '1. We freaked out when we won the lottery. 中了奖券,我们兴奋极了。 2. Congratulations on winning the lottery. 恭喜你中了彩票。', '名词复数: lotteries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('behave', '[bɪ\'heɪv]', 'v.表现；行为；举止', '1. How is your new car behaving? 你的新车性能如何？ 2. I\'ll trust you to behave responsibly while I\'m out. 我相信你在我外出期间会认真办事的。 3. If you behave like that, you\'ll get yourself disliked. 如果你的行为那样，你会让人厌恶的。 4. It\'s hard to train children to behave well at the table. 培养儿童用餐时举止得体是很困难的。', '过去式: behaved 过去分词: behaved 现在分词: behaving 第三人称单数: behaves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disseminate', '[dɪ\'semɪneɪt]', 'vt.散播；公开；宣传', '1. They use the press to disseminate right-wing views. 他们利用报刊来传播右翼观点。 2. It is illegal to disseminate lies. 散布谣言是非法的。 3. It is essential to widely disseminate these ideas among young people. 在青年里面应该广泛地宣传这些思想。', '名词: dissemination 过去式: disseminated 过去分词: disseminated 现在分词: disseminating 第三人称单数: disseminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('toxic', '[\'tɑːksɪk]', 'adj.有毒的', '1. The factory had been sending out toxic fumes. 这家工厂一直在排放有毒的废气。 2. The toxic gas is extremely dangerous. 有毒的汽体是非常地危险的。 3. Too much toxic waste is being dumped at sea. 太多的有毒废料在向大海里倾倒。', '副词: toxically 名词: toxin');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maze', '[meɪz]', 'n.迷宫；曲径；迷惑 vt.使迷惑', '1. We were lost in the maze for several hours. 我们在迷宫里兜了好几个小时出不来。 2. I twisted through a maze of narrow corridors. 我弯弯曲曲地穿行迷宫式的狭窄走廊。 3. The psychologist raced the rats through a long maze. 经过长时间的迷惑心理学家揭穿胡言蜚语。', '过去式: mazed 过去分词: mazed 现在分词: mazing 第三人称单数: mazes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('germ', '[dʒɜːrm]', 'n.细菌；微生物；胚芽', '1. Germs may invade the organism. 细菌会侵入有机体。 2. Germs are invisible to the naked eye. 细菌用肉眼看不见。 3. Disinfectant kills germs. 消毒剂灭杀细菌。 4. This is a ubiquitous germ that lives in nature and can be found in the soil or water. 这是一种在自然界普遍存在的微生物，甚至在土壤和水源中都可以存在。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sticky', '[\'stɪki]', 'adj.粘的；闷热的；困难的；令人不满意的', '1. I am uncomfortable because my body is sticky . 我身上粘粘的，很不舒服。 2. Yuanxiao is a kind of sticky round dumplings. 元宵是一种粘粘的圆的面团。 3. A hot, sticky day makes a person listless. 天气闷热使人觉得身上有气无力。 4. They put me in a sticky position. 他们将我置于一个困难的境地。', '副词: stickily 比较级: stickier 最高级: stickiest 名词: stickiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elective', '[ɪ\'lektɪv]', 'adj.选举的；随意选择的 n.[美]选修科目', '1. He had never held elective office. 他从未担任过任何选举产生的职务。 2. Elective surgery must be carefully investigated. 选择性手术必须小心评估研究。 3. She is taking French as an elective next year. 她明年选修法语。 4. Besides the required courses, I\'m taking an elective in computer. 除了必修课外，我正在选修电脑课。', '副词: electively 名词: electiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sediment', '[\'sedɪmənt]', 'n.沉淀物', '1. He emptied out the water barrel to clear it of sediment. 他把水桶倒空以清掉桶底的沉淀物。 2. If you are replacing the bottom element, remove the accumulated sediment on the bottom of the tank. 如果是拆卸下部加热元件，需要清除累积在内胆底部的沉淀物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sow', '[saʊ]', 'v.播种；散布 n.母猪', '1. These seeds should be sown in April. 这些种子应在四月播种。 2. His words had sowed the seeds of suspicion in their minds. 他的话已在他们心中播下怀疑的种子。 3. The enemy tried to sow discontent among our men . 敌人企图在我们的士兵中间散布不满情绪。', '名词: sower 过去式: sowed 过去分词: sown/sowed 现在分词: sowing 第三人称单数: sows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emblem', '[\'embləm]', 'n.象征；徽章', '1. The bell tower is the emblem of this city. 这座钟楼是这个城市的象征。 2. The dove is an emblem of peace. 鸽子是和平的象征。 3. The presidential seal has an emblem of the eagle. 该总统印章上有一枚老鹰徽章。 4. Every emblem of the Olympics tells a story. 奥林匹克的每块徽章的背后都有一段故事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discharge', '[dɪs\'tʃɑːrdʒ]', 'v.排出；释放；解雇；放电；解除；清偿债务 n.卸货；释放；发射；放电；准许离开；排出物', '1. The Nile discharge itself into the Mediterranean. 尼罗河水注入地中海。 2. The water pipe doesn\'t discharge freely. 水管排水不畅。 3. The judge discharged the prisoner. 法官把囚犯释放了。 4. I am going to discharge our chauffeur. 我要解雇我们的司机。 5. How long will the discharge of the cargo take? 卸货需要多久？', '形容词: dischargeable 名词: dischargee 过去式: discharged 过去分词: discharged 现在分词: discharging 第三人称单数: discharges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sting', '[stɪŋ]', 'vt.刺痛；使苦恼；欺诈 vi.叮；刺痛 n.刺；刺痛；讽刺', '1. Her ingratitude stung him. 她的忘恩负义使他痛心。 2. The smoke began to sting his eyes. 烟开始刺痛他的眼睛。 3. Those harsh words stung me bitterly. 那些严厉的言辞使我感到非常痛苦 4. They used to sting their clients. 他们过去常诈骗客户。 5. It is the nature of the scorpion to sting . 蝎子生下来就会蛰人。 6. A bee pricks the skin with its sting. 蜜蜂用螫针刺皮肤。', '副词: stingingly 过去式: stung 过去分词: stung 现在分词: stinging 第三人称单数: stings');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('supplant', '[sə\'plænt]', 'v. 取代； 排挤 <古>根除', '1. The duke plotted to supplant the king. 公爵阴谋取代国王的地位。 2. She\'s been supplant in her aunt\'s affection by her brother. 她在她姑母心中的地位已被她兄弟取代了。 3. It is my view that the new historical disciplines complement rather than supplant traditional history. 我认为这些新的历史学科对传统历史学起到了补充而非排挤作用。', '过去式: supplanted 过去分词: supplanted 现在分词: supplanting 第三人称单数: supplants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unprecedented', '[ʌn\'presɪdentɪd]', 'adj.空前的；前所未有的', '1. We are seeing unemployment on an unprecedented scale. 我们现在正经历规模空前的失业现象。 2. His statement made an unprecedented splash. 他的声明引起了空前的轰动。 3. The air crash caused an unprecedented number of deaths. 这次空难的死亡人数是空前的。 4. Some economists showed their anxiety on unprecedented level of unemployment. 一些经济学家对失业率达到前所未有的程度表示忧虑。', '副词: unprecedentedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('patent', '[\'pætnt]', 'n.专利；特许 vt.给予专利权 adj.专利的；显著的', '1. The patent runs out in three years time. 这项专利期限为3年。 2. He got a patent for this invention. 他获得了这项发明的专利权。 3. The government patented the device to its inventor. 政府给予发明者专利权。 4. This is a packet of a patent cement mix. 这是一包专利水泥混合料。', '形容词: patentable 名词: patentability 过去式: patented 过去分词: patented 现在分词: patenting 第三人称单数: patents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('valid', '[\'vælɪd]', 'adj.有效的；有根据的；合法的；正当的', '1. Please provide a valid screen name. 请输入有效的显示名。 2. A credit card is not a valid proof of identity. 银行发的支票保付卡不是有效的身份证明文件。 3. Whether or not you believe the lawsuit is fair or valid, it is vital that you act on the summons. 无论这起诉讼是否是公平的或者是有根据的，认真对待传票对当事人来说是至关重要的。 4. The values may be valid,but are not allowed contextually. 提供的值可能是合法的，但是在当前的上下文环境中不被允许。', '副词: validly 名词: validity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emotional', '[ɪ\'moʊʃənl]', 'adj.感情的；情绪的', '1. The conference came to a close with an emotional speech. 会议在有感情的演讲词中结束。 2. They offer each other emotional support. 他们相互提供感情上的支持。 3. I hope her emotional wound will heal with the passing of time. 我希望她感情上的创伤能随时间的流逝而治愈。 4. They made an emotional appeal for help. 他们情绪激动地恳求救助。', '副词: emotionally 名词: emotionality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('persevere', '[ˌpɜːrsə\'vɪr]', 'v.坚持；不屈不挠', '1. When things get difficult, you just have to grit your teeth and persevere. 遇到困难只需咬紧牙关坚持下去。 2. If you persevere with work, you\'ll succeed in the end. 你如果把工作坚持下去，最终会取得成功的。 3. He was hopeless at French, but his teacher persevered with him. 他怎么也学不会法语,可是老师仍锲而不舍地帮助他。', '副词: perseveringly 过去式: persevered 过去分词: persevered 现在分词: persevering 第三人称单数: perseveres');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('communal', '[kə\'mjuːnl]', 'adj.公有的；公社的；共有的', '1. The Plains Indian has a plentiful and regular supply of meat and skins by the communal buffalo hunting. 大草原的印第安人猎取公有的牛而常得到很多肉和皮。 2. In college we had a communal kitchen. 念大学时，我们有共有的厨房。', '副词: communally 名词: communality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lithosphere', '[\'lɪθəsfɪr]', 'n.岩圈；地壳', '1. Scientists call this layer of crust and upper mantle the lithosphere. 科学家称这层地壳和上部地幔为岩石圈。 2. The hydrosphere and the lithosphere together form the Earth\'s surface. 水圈与岩石圈一起形成地球的表面。 3. Below the lithosphere is the rheosphere comprising partly fused peridotite. 岩石圈之下是由部分熔融的橄榄岩所组成的软流圈。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('essential', '[ɪ\'senʃl]', 'adj.本质的；必要的；重要的 n.要素；必需品', '1. This is of course still the essential method. 这当然仍是本质的方法。 2. This is desirable but by no means essential to the primary objective of validating mathematical models of aircraft behaviour. 对于验证飞机性能的数学模型这一主要目的来说，这是必须的，但决不是最本质的. 3. Concentration is essential if you want to do a good job. 如果你想把事情做好,专心是必要的。 4. Mass education is essential in promoting democracy. 民众教育对提倡民主是非常重要的。 5. What are the essentials of good teaching? 成功教学的要素是什么?', '副词: essentially 名词: essentiality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corona', '[kə\'roʊnə]', 'n.日冕；电晕；冠状物；飞檐的上部', '1. The corona gains and loses energy continuously. 日冕总是不断地获得能量和损失能量。 2. Most photographs don\'t adequately portray the magnificence of the Sun\'s corona. 绝大部份的照片,无法把太阳壮丽的日冕忠实地呈现出来。 3. Looking at small details we find that the corona has a delicate structure. 仔细研究细节后，我们发现日冕有精细结构。 4. The discharge state of pulse corona in dedusting differs from of that DC corona. 脉冲电电晕除尘的放电状态不同于传统的直流电除尘。', '名词复数: coronas');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scar', '[skɑːr]', 'n.疤痕；伤痕；断崖 v.结疤；痊愈', '1. He has a scar running across his left cheek. 他左脸上有一道很长的疤痕。 2. The scar flawed her beauty. 这伤疤损害了她的美貌。 3. The cut in her hand has healed completely, without leaving a scar. 她手上的刀伤完全愈合了,没有留下一点伤痕。 4. In that heart, where there had been a wound, there was a scar. 在他的心上，从前有过一条伤口，后来只剩下一条伤痕。 5. The wound gradually scarred over. 伤口渐渐愈合。', '过去式: scarred 过去分词: scarred 现在分词: scarring 第三人称单数: scars');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scholarship', '[\'skɑːlərʃɪp]', 'n.奖学金；学问；学识', '1. The scholarship includes an allowance of 80 dollars for books. 奖学金包括八十美元的书籍费津贴。 2. He won a scholarship to Cambridge. 他获得一份到剑桥大学读书的奖学金。 3. She has been awarded a scholarship to study at Harvard. 她获得了去哈佛大学读书的奖学金。 4. I have not the gifts that are necessary for scholarship. 我没有做学问所必须的天资。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('studio', '[\'stuːdioʊ]', 'n.画室；工作室；播音室；制片厂；摄影场', '1. Upstairs he has a studio where he paints a little. 他在楼上有一个画室，有时在那里作一点画。 2. I was talking to her in the studio. 我那时正在工作室跟它谈话。 3. The studio is being wired for sound. 这个播音室正在安装音响设备用的电线。 4. She must be in the television studio at the moment. 她现在一定在电视演播室。', '名词复数: studios');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ignore', '[ɪɡ\'nɔːr]', 'vt.忽视；不理；不顾', '1. If you ignore your diet, trouble will follow. 如果你忽视自己的饮食，必然会遇到麻烦 2. I agree in principle, but we can\'t ignore the differences. 我原则上同意,但我们不能忽视这些差异。 3. The wisest course would be to ignore it. 上上策是不予理睬。 4. We could ignore him and go direct to the chairman, but we\'d be skating on very thin ice. 我们可以不理会他而直接去找主席，但那样做我们就如履薄冰了。', '形容词: ignorable 名词: ignorer 过去式: ignored 过去分词: ignored 现在分词: ignoring 第三人称单数: ignores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('uppermost', '[\'ʌpərmoʊst]', 'adj.最高的；至上的 adv.向着或在最高或最重要位置', '1. Store this side uppermost. 此面朝上存放。 2. The children\'s future is always uppermost in my mind. 孩子们的前途一向是我心中最重要的事。 3. Oil and truth get uppermost at last. 油脂必定水面浮，真理最终占上风。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ferment', '[\'fɜːrment]', 'n.发酵；酵素；动乱 v.（使）发酵；动乱', '1. He is doing a research in beer ferment. 他正在进行对啤酒发酵的研究。 2. Do health people need edible ferment too? 健康人也需要食用酵素吗？ 3. The country was in ferment. 这个国家处于动荡不安之中。 4. When wine is fermented it gives off bubbles of gas. 酒发酵时会放出气泡。', '形容词: fermentable 名词: fermentability 过去式: fermented 过去分词: fermented 现在分词: fermenting 第三人称单数: ferments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('script', '[skrɪpt]', 'n.剧本；脚本；手稿；手迹；字体；考卷', '1. The script won\'t play well. 那个剧本不适于在舞台上演出。 2. If the trust is verified, the script runs. 如果确定可信,则会运行该脚本。 3. The truthfulness of the script is undoubtable. 手稿的真实性是毋庸置疑的。 4. Sanskrit historically has had no single script associated with it. 梵语，从历史上看，没有单一的手稿与它联合起来。', '过去式: scripted 过去分词: scripted 现在分词: scripting 第三人称单数: scripts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('respond', '[rɪ\'spɑːnd]', 'v.回答；响应；反应；反应灵敏；反响 n.[建]壁联；[宗]应唱圣歌', '1. I invited her to dinner but she did not respond. 我请她吃晚饭，但她未作回答。 2. The screen is sensitive and can respond to slight touch. 触摸屏反应灵敏,能响应轻微的触碰。 3. He tried to be amusing, but I didn\'t respond. 他试图逗乐,可我一点都没反应。 4. The car responds well to the controls. 这辆汽车操纵灵敏.', '名词: responder 过去式: responded 过去分词: responded 现在分词: responding 第三人称单数: responds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appetite', '[\'æpɪtaɪt]', 'n.食欲；嗜好；欲望', '1. She is suffering from lack of appetite. 她食欲不振。 2. The long walk has given me a good appetite. 走了长路使我食欲大振。 3. Mary has no appetite for hard work. 玛丽不想干艰苦的工作。 4. I have to make an effort to work up an appetite for reading. 我得努力使自己产生天天想读书的愿望。', '形容词: appetitive');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reward', '[rɪ\'wɔːrd]', 'n.报答；赏金；报酬 vt.奖赏；给 ... 报酬', '1. An act of kindness deserves a reward. 做好事,当然要有报答。 2. By rights, half the reward should be mine. 按理说，有一半奖赏应该是我的。 3. You have received a just reward. 你已得到了应有的报酬。 4. They rewarded the winners with gifts of fruits and flowers. 他们奖给优胜者一些水果和鲜花。', '形容词: rewardable 名词: rewarder 过去式: rewarded 过去分词: rewarded 现在分词: rewarding 第三人称单数: rewards');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mushroom', '[\'mʌʃrʊm]', 'n.蘑菇；菌菇状物；暴发户 vi.采蘑菇；雨后春笋般涌现；迅速增加', '1. Some mushrooms are poisonous. 有些蘑菇有毒。 2. I gathered many mushrooms after rain. 雨后我采了很多蘑菇。 3. The mushroom cloud of the A-bomb hung over the desert again. 原子弹爆炸的蘑菇云再度笼罩在沙漠的上空。 4. Mushroom clouds appear after nuclear explosions. 核弹爆炸后会产生蘑菇云。 5. Let\'s go mushrooming. 我们采蘑菇去吧。', '过去式: mushroomed 过去分词: mushroomed 现在分词: mushrooming 第三人称单数: mushrooms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gorgeous', '[\'ɡɔːrdʒəs]', 'adj.华丽的；灿烂的；极好的', '1. The gorgeous costume added to the brilliance of the dance. 华丽的服装使舞蹈更加光彩夺目。 2. In the evening the rosy clouds were gorgeous. 傍晚的云霞绚丽多彩。 3. The garden is gorgeous with peonies. 花园里盛开着绚丽的牡丹花。 4. What a gorgeous day! 多美好的一天啊!', '副词: gorgeously 名词: gorgeousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('further', '[\'fɜːrðər]', 'adj.更远的 adv.进一步地；此外 v.促进；推动', '1. Our object is to further strengthen friendly relations between the two countries. 我们的目标是进一步加强两国之间的友好关系。 2. Further, it is important to consider the cost of repairs. 此外，重要的是要考虑修理费用。 3. They hoped the new venture would further the cause of cultural cooperation in Europe. 他们希望这个新项目将促进欧洲文化合作事业。 4. The ambitious young man used his friends to further his career. 这位野心勃勃的年轻人利用朋友来推动他的事业的发展。', '名词: furtherer 过去式: furthered 过去分词: furthered 现在分词: furthering 第三人称单数: furthers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('definite', '[\'defɪnət]', 'adj.明确的；一定的；有把握的', '1. His vague ideas crystallized into a definite plan. 他那些模糊的想法变成了一个明确的计划。 2. The workers demand a definite answer. 工人们要求一个明确的答复。 3. You have our definite support. 我们绝对支持您。 4. It\'s definite that he will win. 他肯定会赢。', '副词: definitely 名词: definiteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complete', '[kəm\'pliːt]', 'adj.完整的；完成的；彻底的 vt.完成；使完美；使圆满；填（表格等）', '1. We\'ll certainly set up a complete modern industrial system. 我们一定要建立一个完整的现代化工业体系。 2. When the experiment is complete, include your findings in a report. 试验完成後,请把结果写入报告。 3. This is a complete failure. 这是一个彻底的失败。 4. Can you complete your task on time? 你们能按时完成工作吗?', '形容词: completive 副词: completely 比较级: completer 最高级: completest 名词: completeness 过去式: completed 过去分词: completed 现在分词: completing 第三人称单数: completes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('snap', '[snæp]', 'v.劈啪作响；崩塌；砰然关上；猛咬；谩骂；拍摄 n.啪嗒声；快照 adj.突然的；匆忙的 adv.劈啪作响地', '1. Most pine snaps as it burns. 大多数松木燃烧时都发出断裂声。 2. The violin string snapped because it was fastened too tight. 小提琴的弦上得太紧，突然断了。 3. This final misfortune caused his mind to snap. 最后这次不幸事件使他的精神一下子崩溃了。 4. The shark snapped its jaws shut. 鲨鱼啪嗒一声把嘴合上了。 5. The snap of a twig broke the silence. 一根树枝突然折断打破了寂静。 6. They carried out a snap check on the expense account. 他们对费用户口进行了突然的审查。 7. Suddenly the oar went snap. 桨突然啪的一声断了。', '过去式: snapped 过去分词: snapped 现在分词: snapping 第三人称单数: snaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('metric', '[\'metrɪk]', 'adj.公制的；米制的；十进制的 n.标准；度量', '1. Britain changed to a metric system of currency in 1970. 1970年,英国已改用公制货币。 2. Most countries adopt metric system. 大多数国家采用米制。 3. Government departments use metric units exclusively. 政府部门现已全面采用十进制单位。 4. Extensibility is a difficult metric to gauge. 可扩展性是一个比较难衡量的标准。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ethnic', '[\'eθnɪk]', 'adj.种族的；民族的；有民族特色的 n.少数民族的一员', '1. Canada is a multicultural country. Regardless of your ethnic origin, you will feel at home in Canada; 加拿大是一个多元文化国家,无论你为何种族,在加拿大你都会感到安适; 2. Along the way, tourists can see the Tujia ethnic minorities tilling the land. 沿着这条路,旅游者可以看到土家族的人在耕地。 3. That\'s why you can find almost every kind of ethnic food in America. 那也就是为什么在美国你几乎可以看到所有不同民族的食物。 4. Now all the 55 ethnic minorities have their own college students,and some even are master\'s and doctor\'s degree holders. 目前，55个少数民族都有了本民族的大学生，有的还有了硕士生和博士生。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prairie', '[\'preri]', 'n.大草原', '1. The prairie is topped occasionally by low hills. 偶尔可见大草原上隆起几座低矮的小山。 2. A cowboy fell off his horse and broke his leg on the prairie. 一个牛仔在大草原上从马背上摔了下来，摔断了腿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('melting', '[\'meltɪŋ]', 'adj.融化的 动词melt的现在分词.', '1. Melting snow feeds the reservoirs. 融化的雪给水库提供了水 2. The mountain climber could not find many footholds on the melting ice. 登山者在融化的冰上找不到多少立足之处。 3. The valley is continuously watered by the melting snow from the mountains. 群山融化的雪不断流经山谷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revise', '[rɪ\'vaɪz]', 'n.校订；修正；再校稿 v.校订；修正；校正', '1. A method to revise the radius of switch probes is also put forward. 此外还提出了一种修正开关式球测头半径的计量学方法。 2. The market turmoil has spurred economists to revise their forecasts. 当前的市场动荡已促使经济学家们重新修正自己的预测数据。 3. A method to revise the radius of switch probes is also put forward. 此外还提出了一种修正开关式球测头半径的计量学方法。 4. The market turmoil has spurred economists to revise their forecasts. 当前的市场动荡已促使经济学家们重新修正自己的预测数据。', '形容词: revisable 名词: reviser 过去式: revised 过去分词: revised 现在分词: revising 第三人称单数: revises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('astonish', '[ə\'stɑːnɪʃ]', 'vt.使惊讶；使吃惊', '1. I was astonished at the news of his escape. 听到他逃之夭夭的消息，我感到惊讶。 2. She astonished me with her beautiful handwriting. 她以其秀丽的书法而使我惊异。 3. A matter of repeated occurrence like this will not astonish people. 重复出现的事物不会使人吃惊。', '副词: astonishingly 过去式: astonished 过去分词: astonished 现在分词: astonishing 第三人称单数: astonishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frown', '[fraʊn]', 'n.皱眉；不悦 v.不同意；皱眉头', '1. We interpret a frown as a sign of disapproval. 我们把皱眉当作不赞成的表示。 2. The frown on the man\'s face showed that he was displeased. 那人皱着眉头，面露不悦。 3. There was a deep frown of his face. 他的额头深深的皱眉。 4. Her beautiful face had a resentful frown on it. 她那俊俏的眉梢怨恨地蹙了起来。 5. He would frown on such a proposal. 他不会赞成这样的建议。', '副词: frowningly 名词: frowner 过去式: frowned 过去分词: frowned 现在分词: frowning 第三人称单数: frowns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('version', '[\'vɜːrʒn]', 'n.版本；说法；译本；形式', '1. The new version of this dictionary is not in use yet. 这本字典的新版本还未通行。 2. The two newspapers gave different versions of what happened. 两家报纸对发生的事说法不一。 3. The book was translated into many versions and sold all over the world. 这本书被翻译成多种译文并行销全球。 4. This shirt is a cheaper version of the one I saw in that shop. 这件衬衫同我在那家商店里见到的几乎一样，但它是便宜货。', '形容词: versional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dazzle', '[\'dæzl]', 'v.使眼花；使赞许 n.光辉', '1. His eyes dazzled before the strong light. 他面对强光头晕目眩。 2. She was dazzled by her sudden success. 突然的成功使她感到迷惘。 3. The diamond ring worn in her bridle hand\'s third finger dazzle against firelight. 她左手无名指上戴的钻石戒指在火光下闪闪发亮。 4. You will dazzle everyone you meet this week. 遇到的每个人都会为你倾倒。 5. The theatre was a dazzle of bright lights. 剧院是一片光芒耀眼的明亮灯光。', '副词: dazzlingly 名词: dazzler 过去式: dazzled 过去分词: dazzled 现在分词: dazzling 第三人称单数: dazzles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('naked', '[\'neɪkɪd]', 'adj.裸体的；无掩饰的；明白的；无覆盖的', '1. These little boys swim naked in the river. 这些小孩光着身子在河里游泳。 2. The men of this tribe used to go naked. 这个部落里的男子过去常是裸体的。 3. Craft must have clothes,but truth love to go naked. 欺诈必须伪装，真理不须掩饰。 4. This in itself is naked deprivation [of rights]. 这本身就是赤裸裸的剥夺。', '副词: nakedly 名词: nakedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fluctuate', '[\'flʌktʃueɪt]', 'vi.波动；动摇；起伏 vt.使动摇', '1. Fruit prices fluctuate with the seasons. 水果价格随着季节波动。 2. Some investors panic when stock prices fluctuate wildly. 当股票价格大幅波动时,一些投资者便开始恐慌起来。 3. While the psychological unbalance may fluctuate the individual\'s original philosophy and regular act tendency which make conditions for the naissance of aberrance. 而心理的失衡极大地动摇了个体原有的人生观和行为定势 ,为越轨行为的产生创造了条件。 4. Both the light and radio outputs fluctuate markedly. 光和无线电的输出都引人注目地起伏变化。', '形容词: fluctuant 名词: fluctuation 过去式: fluctuated 过去分词: fluctuated 现在分词: fluctuating 第三人称单数: fluctuates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detest', '[dɪ\'test]', 'v.厌恶；痛恨', '1. I detest all affectation. 我厌恶一切矫揉造作的行为。 2. She detests having to talk to people at parties. 她讨厌在宴会上为应酬而和人交谈。 3. I detest people who tell lies. 我痛恨撒谎的人。 4. I detest violence with my whole being. 我毕生谴责暴力行为。', '名词: detester 过去式: detested 过去分词: detested 现在分词: detesting 第三人称单数: detests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thorn', '[θɔːrn]', 'n.刺；荆棘', '1. She got her finger pricked by a thorn. 她的手指被刺扎了一下。 2. One puts on gloves before grasping a thorn cudgel. 为了要握有刺的棍子，首先得戴上手套。 3. Priestesses are immune to their own thorn effects. 女祭司不会受自己创造的荆棘刺影响。 4. And still, we choose the pain of the thorn. 我们仍然选择了那痛苦的荆棘。', '形容词: thornless');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outstanding', '[aʊt\'stændɪŋ]', 'adj.优秀的；突出的；未支付的；未完成的', '1. He was an outstanding student. 他是个优秀的学生。 2. Given the chance, John might have become an outstanding painter. 如果有机会,约翰也许已成为一位杰出的画家了。 3. Two things are outstanding in the creation of the English system of canals. 在创建英国运河体系的过程中,有两件事是非常突出的。 4. 75 per cent of the amount originally borrowed is still outstanding. 最初的借款仍有75%25 未偿还。', '副词: outstandingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disciple', '[dɪ\'saɪpl]', 'n.弟子；门徒；信徒', '1. The sage asked this disciple to wait. 智者让这个弟子等一会儿。 2. Matthew had just been called as a disciple. 马太刚被呼召作耶稣的门徒。 3. I\'m putting my shirt on Devil\'s Disciple to win the next race. 我这所有的钱都押在魔鬼门徒这匹马，指望它赢下一场比赛上了。 4. He was an ardent disciple of Gandhi. 他是甘地的忠实信徒。', '名词: discipleship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accost', '[ə\'kɔːst]', 'v.搭话；搭讪', '1. She is too shy to dare accost him. 她太害羞了,不敢和他搭话。 2. She was accosted by a complete stranger. 有一个她完全不认识的人过来和她搭讪。', '过去式: accosted 过去分词: accosted 现在分词: accosting 第三人称单数: accosts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('noticeable', '[\'noʊtɪsəbl]', 'adj.显而易见的；显著的；值得注意的', '1. The scar on her forehead is hardly noticeable. 她额头上的伤疤不太明显。 2. There\'s been a noticeable improvement in her handwriting. 她的书法有了明显的进步。 3. His good humour was particularly noticeable. 他的幽默感是显而易见的。 4. The specialists did not uncover any noticeable deviations from the norm. 专科医师并未发现任何值得注意的异状。', '副词: noticeably 名词: noticeability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hover', '[\'hʌvər]', 'v.盘旋；徘徊；靠近（某事物），维持在某种不确定的状态 n.盘旋', '1. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。 2. After the alien spacecraft had hovered over the park for a short time, it vanished. 那只外星来的宇宙飞船在公园上空盘旋了一会儿之后就不见了。 3. He hovered nervously in the doorway. 他在门口紧张地来回踱步。 4. The mercury hovered around 35 Celsius degree. 水银温度计停留在摄氏35度左右。 5. He felt creeping of fate, the circling of wolves, the hover of vultures. 他感到厄运已经来到，豺狼正在包围，秃鹰也在盘旋。', '副词: hoveringly 名词: hoverer 过去式: hovered 过去分词: hovered 现在分词: hovering 第三人称单数: hovers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detached', '[dɪ\'tætʃt]', 'adj.超然的；分离的；独立的', '1. Our persuasion did not alter his detached opinion. 我们的劝说没有改变他超然的意见。 2. He took a detached attitude to the matter. 他对那件事持超然的态度。 3. Is the name of the database to be detached. 要分离的数据库的名称。 4. It is also possible that the nidus of the osteochondral loose body was a completely detached portion of calcified ligamentum flavum. 骨软骨游离体的病灶很可能是一段完全分离的黄韧带。', '副词: detachedly 名词: detachedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enclose', '[ɪn\'kloʊz]', 'vt.圈起；围住；附上；封入', '1. He enclosed the land with a hedge. 他用篱笆把地圈起来。 2. Farmers often enclose their land with hedges. 农夫们常用树篱将他们的地围起来。 3. With respect to your enquiry, I enclose an explanatory leaflet. 关于你的询问,兹附上有关说明资料。 4. We enclose a list showing our present availability. 兹附上我方现时可以供应的货单一张。', '异体字: inclose 过去式: enclosed 过去分词: enclosed 现在分词: enclosing 第三人称单数: encloses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confirm', '[kən\'fɜːrm]', 'v.证实；批准；确定', '1. His letter confirmed everything. 他的信证实了一切。 2. The treaty was confirmed by the president. 条约已被总统批准。 3. Could you confirm the dispatch date? 您可以确定发货日期吗?', '形容词: confirmable 名词: confirmability 过去式: confirmed 过去分词: confirmed 现在分词: confirming 第三人称单数: confirms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deft', '[deft]', 'adj.敏捷熟练的；灵巧的', '1. She is deft at dealing with reporters. 她善於与记者周旋。 2. Sister Irene was a tall, deft woman in her early thirties. 艾琳修女是个三十出头、精明能干的高个妇女。 3. With deft fingers she untangled the wire. 她用灵巧的手指解开了金属线。 4. My sister is a clever and deft person who can make pretty dresses. 姐姐是个心灵手巧的人，做的衣服很漂亮。', '副词: deftly 比较级: defter 最高级: deftest 名词: deftness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concerted', '[kən\'sɜːtɪd]', 'adj.协定的；商议好的；一致的 动词concert的过去式和过去分词.', '1. As if this had been a concerted signal, the back door was struck rudely. 仿佛是在按照一个事先约定好的信号行事,后门顿时被不客气地捶了起来。 2. If we reach a consensus, we can make concerted efforts. 思想认识统一了，大家就一致行动。 3. There has been a concerted campaign against the proposals. 人们将采取一致行动反对这些提议。', '副词: concertedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('egoist', '[\'iːɡoʊɪst]', 'n.自我主义者；利己主义者', '1. John is such an egoist that he only cares about himself. 约翰过于自我,只在乎自己。 2. The egoist used other people as if they were doormats. 那个利己主义者总是利用别人', '形容词: egoistic 副词: egoistically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('molecule', '[\'mɑːlɪkjuːl]', 'n.分子；微粒', '1. A molecule is made up of atoms. 分子由原子组成。 2. Two atoms of hydrogen combine with one atom of oxygen to form a molecule of water. 两个氢原子和一个氧原子结合而成一个水分子。 3. We can see many molecules flying in the air when a sunbeam penetrated the dark room. 当一束光线穿进暗淡的房间时，我们可以看到空气中有许多小颗粒在飞舞。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('myriad', '[\'mɪriəd]', 'adj.无数的 n.极大数量', '1. There are myriad fish in the ocean. 海里有无数的鱼。 2. Myriad stars are twinkling in the night sky. 无数的星星在夜空中闪烁著。 3. Designs are available in a myriad of colours. 各种色彩的款式应有尽有。 4. I had three weeks to make a myriad of arrangements. 我花了3个星期做大量准备工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('saturate', '[\'sætʃəreɪt]', 'v.使浸透；使充满；使饱和 adj.浸透的；饱和的；深颜色的', '1. We lay on the beach, saturated in sunshine. 我们躺在沙滩上，沐浴在阳光里。 2. We were caught in the rain and came home saturated. 我们挨了雨淋, 回家时已浑身湿透。 3. The air was saturated with the perfume of the flowers. 空气中飘荡着花香。 4. The films manufactured by Hollywood are saturated in the cinemas all over the world. 在全世界电影市场上充斥着好莱坞的影片。', '形容词: saturable 名词: saturator 过去式: saturated 过去分词: saturated 现在分词: saturating 第三人称单数: saturates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scan', '[skæn]', 'vt.扫描；浏览；审视；细看 vi.合韵律；划分音步 n.扫描；浏览；细看', '1. Could you teach me how to scan an image? 你可以教我如何扫描一个影像吗? 2. I scanned the newspaper when I was waiting for the bus. 等公共汽车的时候，我匆匆浏览了一下报纸。 3. She scanned his face, looking for signs of what he was thinking. 她审视他的脸,试图探寻他在思考什么。 4. I scanned my pocket for change. 我仔细查看囗袋找零钱。 5. The verses scan well. 这些诗句符合韵律。 6. The doctors gave him an ultrasonic brain scan. 医生给他做了脑部超声波扫描检查。', '形容词: scannable 名词: scanner 过去式: scanned 过去分词: scanned 现在分词: scanning 第三人称单数: scans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('medal', '[\'medl]', 'n.奖章；勋章；纪念章 vi.获得奖章', '1. He got a medal for bravery. 他因勇敢而获得一枚奖章。 2. She was awarded a medal for bravery. 她因勇敢而获得奖章。 3. He got a medal for his gallantry. 他因勇敢而赢得一枚勋章。 4. The soldier earned a medal for bravery. 这名战士因作战勇敢而获得了勋章。 5. Winning the medal was a feather in his cap. 获得奖章是他的荣誉。', '形容词: medallic 过去式: medaled/medalled 过去分词: medaled/medalled 现在分词: medaling/medalling 第三人称单数: medals/medals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('leash', '[liːʃ]', 'n.(系狗的)皮带；控制；约束 n.（打猎用语）三只；三个一组 v.用皮带控制；束缚', '1. Beau was pulling ahead of me with his leash. 博套着皮带拽着我走在前面。 2. He slipped the hound from the leash. 他解开皮带放掉猎狗。 3. The memes take hold of the leash. 迷因控制了基因。 4. Our parent company keeps us on a fairly short leash. 我们的母公司对我们的控制相当紧。 5. This is the phylosopher\'s mind off the leash. 这是哲学家思想摆脱了束缚结果。', '过去式: leashed 过去分词: leashed 现在分词: leashing 第三人称单数: leashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resort', '[rɪ\'zɔːrt]', 'n.(度假)胜地；手段；凭借 vi.诉诸；常去', '1. The island is a favorite summer resort for tourists. 这座岛是旅游者的避暑胜地。 2. Its unique natural scenery makes it an ideal holiday resort. 独具特色的自然景观,使这里成为度假休闲的理想胜地。 3. A carriage was the only resort. 乘马车是唯一的办法。 4. The resort to force is forbidden in this school. 该学校禁止动武。 5. If other means fail，we shall resort to force. 如果其他手段均失败,我们就将诉诸武力。', '过去式: resorted 过去分词: resorted 现在分词: resorting 第三人称单数: resorts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('admirable', '[\'ædmərəbl]', 'adj.令人钦佩的；令人赞赏的', '1. His bravery is admirable. 他的勇气令人钦佩。 2. She showed admirable self-control. 她表现出令人钦佩的自我控制。 3. This essay is admirable in all respects. 这篇文章在各方面都很值得欣赏。 4. It was reserved for him to make the admirable discovery. 那项令人赞赏的发现注定由他完成。', '副词: admirably 名词: admirableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preferable', '[\'prefrəbl]', 'adj.更好的；更合意的', '1. To be honest, I\'ve got a preferable offer. 老实说，我有唯一更好的任务机遇。', '副词: preferably 名词: preferability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squander', '[\'skwɑːndər]', 'vt.浪费；挥霍', '1. It\'s a crime to squander our country\'s natural resources. 浪费我们国家的自然资源是一种罪恶 2. Don\'t squander your affection on him, he\'ll never love you. 不要把感情浪费在他身上，他是永远不会爱你的。 3. He has squandered all his savings on drink. 他把存的钱全买酒喝了。 4. Addictions are good ways to squander wealth and health. 上瘾是挥霍健康和金钱的好办法。', '副词: squanderingly 名词: squanderer 过去式: squandered 过去分词: squandered 现在分词: squandering 第三人称单数: squanders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fungus', '[\'fʌŋɡəs]', 'n.真菌；霉菌 （复数为funguses或fungi).', '1. My roses were suffering from fungus. 我的玫瑰受到真菌的侵害。 2. This is evidently a xerophytic fungus. 它显然是一种旱生真菌。 3. There are many different types of fungus all over the world. 世界上有多种不同类型的霉菌。 4. Here is an Aspergillus fungus ball in a dilated bronchus. 这里是扩张支气管内的一个曲霉菌真菌球。', '名词复数: fungi');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('address', '[ə\'dres]', 'n.住址；网址；电子邮箱地址；称呼；致词；讲话；演讲；谈吐 v.称呼；发表演说；提出；写地址；处理', '1. Please write your home address on the registration form. 请在这张登记表上写下你的家庭住址。 2. I\'ll log in to the internet to know about you. I know your address. 我还是上因特网去看吧，我知道你们的网址。 3. Can you tell me your E-mail address? 能告诉我你的电子邮箱地址吗? 4. What form of address should one use when writing to a bishop? 给主教写信应该怎样称呼? 5. Most people call me Bob. How do I address you? 大家叫我鲍勃,我怎么称呼你?', '过去式: addressed 过去分词: addressed 现在分词: addressing 第三人称单数: addresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conceit', '[kən\'siːt]', 'n.自负；个人观点；幻想；字字珠玑；好评', '1. This young man is full of conceit. 这个年轻人非常自负。 2. No one admires a man who is full of conceit. 没有人喜欢一个十分自负的人。 3. He jotted down his conceits of his idle hours. 他记下闲暇时自己想到的一些念头。 4. I don\'t have much conceit of his poems. 我对他的诗作没有什么好评。', '过去式: conceited 过去分词: conceited 现在分词: conceiting 第三人称单数: conceits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discrete', '[dɪ\'skriːt]', 'adj.不连续的；分离的', '1. They give off discrete amounts of radiant energy. 它们放出不连续的辐射能量。 2. The proteins initially appear as discrete bodies. 蛋白质体最初作为分离体而出现。', '副词: discretely 名词: discreteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tutor', '[\'tuːtər]', 'n.家庭教师；导师 v.指导；当家庭教师；当导师', '1. His parents employed a tutor to teach him Greek. 他父母雇佣了一位家庭教师来教他希腊语。 2. My tutor is an accomplished scholar. 我的导师是一位学识渊博的学者。 3. Most parents have no time to tutor their children. 大部分家长没有时间辅导孩子。 4. For extra money, she tutors on weekends. 为了多挣些钱，她在周末当家庭教师。', '过去式: tutored 过去分词: tutored 现在分词: tutoring 第三人称单数: tutors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mechanist', '[\'mekəˌnɪst]', 'n.机械技师；机械学者；机械论者', '1. We have many engineers and mechanist with rich experiences. 作为专业水处理设备制造公司，我们能供应各种类型和规格的水处理设备。 2. Objective:To research the functional mechanist of Children Cough Pellet(CCP)and to evaluate its clinical efficacy. 目的:评价小儿止咳颗粒治疗小儿咳嗽变异性哮喘的临床疗效。 3. Answer me, mechanist, has Nature arranged all the springs of feeling in this animal to the end that he might not feel? 那麽，说动物是机械论者，请告诉我，自然之母难道给了这只动物所有感觉的泉源，却不容许牠有感觉？ 4. Such pathologies in modern classroom as domination,separation and linearity may be attributed to the dominant mechanist views. 机械论与生态论是截然不同的两种宇宙论,控制、分离与线性等现代课堂病理都可归为机械论主导。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hoax', '[hoʊks]', 'v.欺骗；哄骗；愚弄 n.愚弄人；恶作剧', '1. All hoax viruses are essentially chain letters. 所有的欺骗性病毒基本都是连续性的字母。 2. Some posters on Chinese bulletin boards and blogs have argued that Mr Zhou was perhaps merely a hapless tool in a hoax perpetrated mainly by bureaucrats. 一些中文的贴子和博客提出，周也许不过是官方欺骗闹剧中的一个不幸的工具而已。 3. Mainstream critics argue that the entire affair is a hoax. 主流的批评家批评整件事是一场愚弄。 4. Authorities call the apparent hoax reprehensible, but even with just five feet. 官方称这是明显的愚弄行为，应该遭受斥责，但是仍然还有五只断脚。 5. They considered the phone call a hoax. 他们认为那个电话是恶作剧。', '名词: hoaxer 过去式: hoaxed 过去分词: hoaxed 现在分词: hoaxing 第三人称单数: hoaxes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hilarity', '[hɪ\'lærəti]', 'n.欢喜；高兴；兴高采烈', '1. Sasha\'s on court passion borders on hilarity. 萨沙在比赛场上展现出来的激情可以用狂欢来形容。 2. Wine gives not light hilarity, but noisy merriment 酒不给人以轻松的欢乐，而给人以嚣嚷的狂欢。 3. The announcement was greeted with much hilarity and mirth. 这一项宣布引起了热烈的欢呼声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stem', '[stem]', 'n.柄；茎；干；船首 vi.起源于 vt.抽去 ... 的梗；给 ... 装柄；逆 ... 而行；阻止，遏制', '1. Don\'t eat the stem of a mushroom. 不要吃蘑菇的梗。 2. This is a plant stem that has been pithed. 这是一根已经除去木髓的植物的茎。 3. Crime and punishment grow out of one stem. 罪与罚本是同茎生。 4. She bought some roses with long stems. 她买了一些枝干很长的玫瑰花。 5. Your errors stem all from your carelessness. 你犯的错误全都是由于你的粗心。 6. Our ship stemmed on against the current. 我们的船逆流而上。', '过去式: stemmed 过去分词: stemmed 现在分词: stemming 第三人称单数: stems');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('likewise', '[\'laɪkwaɪz]', 'adv.同样地；此外；（表示感觉相同）我也是', '1. Watch him and do likewise. 注意看着他然后照样做。 2. I told him to watch me and do likewise. 我叫他仔细看著我,并且照样做。 3. She sprinkled her with the juices of aconite, and immediately her hair came off, and her nose and ears likewise. 她用附子汁向阿拉喀涅洒去，她的头发马上就脱光了，她的鼻子和耳朵也掉了。 4. They went on foot and I did likewise. 他们步行去,我也步行去了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('liberate', '[\'lɪbəreɪt]', 'v.解放；使获得自由；释出；放出', '1. The country was liberated in 1966. 这个国家是在1966年解放的。 2. Our army had liberated many occupied areas. 我们的军队解放了许多地区。 3. This small software can liberate your fingers! 这个小软件可以解放你的手指啦！ 4. They can liberate us from the limitations of our thoughts and feelings. 他们可以使我们从思想与感受解放。', '副词: liberatingly 名词: liberator 过去式: liberated 过去分词: liberated 现在分词: liberating 第三人称单数: liberates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accuracy', '[\'ækjərəsi]', 'n.准确(性)；精确度', '1. He\'s a man of accuracy and strict method. 他是个精细而严谨的人。 2. Accuracy is more important than speed in his new job. 对他的新工作，准确比速度更重要。 3. I can predict something with great accuracy. 我能很准确地预测某事。 4. It is impossible to say with any accuracy how many are affected. 无论如何也说不准受影响的有多少。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detain', '[dɪ\'teɪn]', 'vt.扣留；拘押；耽搁；延误', '1. You cannot detain the eagle in the forest. 你没有法子将一只老鹰扣留在森林里。 2. We shall have to detain him and question him. 我们只好把他扣起来，讯问他一下。 3. Allow me to detain you for a moment. 请允许我耽搁你一会儿。 4. This matter isn\'t very important, and shouldn\'t detain us very long. 这事不很重要，不该耽搁我们很久。', '名词: detainment 过去式: detained 过去分词: detained 现在分词: detaining 第三人称单数: detains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bump', '[bʌmp]', 'v.碰撞；颠簸而行；提高 n.肿块；撞击；表面隆起 adv.突然的；猛烈的', '1. I\'ve bumped my knee on the wall. 我的膝盖撞上了墙壁。 2. I am so sorry to bump into you. 对不起，我撞到你了。 3. The old bus bumped along the mountain road. 旧公共汽车沿著山路颠簸行驶。 4. We bumped up and down along the gravel path. 我们沿砾石小路颠簸而行。 5. She got a bump on her head. 她头上撞起了一个包。', '过去式: bumped 过去分词: bumped 现在分词: bumping 第三人称单数: bumps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equal', '[\'iːkwəl]', 'adj.相等的；平等的 vt.比得上；等于 n.同辈；平等；(同等的)人或事物', '1. Women demand equal pay for equal work. 妇女要求同工同酬。 2. All countries, big and small, should be equal. 国家不论大小, 一律平等。 3. Nobody can equal him in intelligence. 没有人在智力方面能比得上他。 4. Three and five equals eight. 三加五等于八。 5. They are my equals in age. 我和他们是同龄人。', '副词: equally 过去式: equaled/equalled 过去分词: equaled/equalled 现在分词: equaling/equalling 第三人称单数: equals/equals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('racket', '[\'rækɪt]', 'n.球拍 n.喧闹；敲诈；<俚>行业；职业 v.喧闹；花天酒地', '1. The ball just tipped the edge of his racket. 球仅仅碰到他球拍的边儿。 2. My hands blistered from holding the racket. 我的手因握球拍而起了水疱。 3. What a racket the children are making! 这些孩子太吵了！ 4. The students kicked up no end of a racket in the street. 这些学生在大街上大吵大闹。 5. The children always racket about in the courtyard. 孩子们总是在院子里吵吵闹闹。', '过去式: racketed 过去分词: racketed 现在分词: racketing 第三人称单数: rackets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('role', '[roʊl]', 'n.作用；角色', '1. The Panama Canal has played a very important role in transportation. 巴拿马运河在运输上起到了非常重要的作用。 2. The key role of the teacher in the learning process should not be neglected. 教师在学习中的关键作用是不该忽视的。 3. The role of the railway declines in the transport system. 在运输系统中,铁路的重要性逐渐下降。 4. She prefers to play comic roles. 她更喜欢扮演滑稽角色。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('media', '[\'miːdiə]', 'n.传播媒介；(medium的复数)媒体；新闻媒介', '1. Tim appeared unabashed by all the media attention. 蒂姆成了传播媒介的焦点，却也满不在乎。 2. The media have a lot of power today. 现在大众传播媒介有很大的力量。 3. The actress revels in all the attention she gets from the media. 这位女演员陶醉于传媒对她的吹捧。 4. The president created media hype by visiting cities down south. 总统访问南部乡下,制造媒体宣传。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compensation', '[ˌkɑːmpen\'seɪʃn]', 'n.补偿；赔偿；赔偿金', '1. My job is hard,but it has its compensations.It is a great delight to pursue what I am interested in. 我拍的工作虽苦,但也有所补偿。能够从事我感兴趣的工作让我很开心。 2. Compensation of injured workers has cost the company a lot. 公司花了一大笔钱赔偿受伤的工人。 3. My job is hard, but it has its compensations—it is my happiness to pursue what I am interested in. 我的工作虽苦,但却有所补偿（有好的方面因而不觉得太苦）。', '形容词: compensational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('starve', '[stɑːrv]', 'vi.挨饿；受饿；极度匮乏 vt.使挨饿；使饿死', '1. They were suffered to starve on the pavement. 他们流流街头，忍饥挨饿。 2. They would starve if food was difficult to find. 如果很难找到食物，他们就会挨饿。 3. They would rather starve than give way. 他们宁愿饿死也不妥协。 4. The explorers starved to death in the desert. 探险者们在沙漠中饿死了。 5. It is silly to starve yourself to be skinny. 显得有骨感而挨饿是愚蠢的.', '过去式: starved 过去分词: starved 现在分词: starving 第三人称单数: starves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exist', '[ɪɡ\'zɪst]', 'v.存在；生存；活着', '1. Most scientists believe that water doesn\'t exist on the surface of the moon. 多数科学家认为,月球表面不存在水。 2. That department has ceased to exist. 那部门已不复存在。 3. Man cannot exist without air. 没有空气人就不能生存。 4. The old lady exists only on rice coffee and bread. 老太太仅靠咖啡面包生活。', '过去式: existed 过去分词: existed 现在分词: existing 第三人称单数: exists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recession', '[rɪ\'seʃn]', 'n.后退；（经济）不景气', '1. A few days later, there was a gradual recession of flood waters. 几天之后,洪水逐渐消退。 2. The recession has caused thousands of bankruptcy. 经济不景气造成数千万的破产。 3. There is no sign that the recession has bottomed out yet. 没有迹象表明萧条已经到了极点。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('weed', '[wiːd]', 'n.杂草；野草 n.衣服；丧服 vi.除草；清除；淘汰', '1. The garden is choked with weeds. 花园杂草丛生。 2. She knelt down to pull a weed from the flower bed. 她跪下来拔除花圃上的杂草。 3. There are so many weeds in his field! 他的田里有那么多野草！ 4. He pulled off his coat and started to weed with us. 他脱去上装，开始和我们一起除草。', '过去式: weeded 过去分词: weeded 现在分词: weeding 第三人称单数: weeds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('correct', '[kə\'rekt]', 'adj.正确的；得体的 v.改正；纠正', '1. Your answer to the question is correct. 你对这个问题的回答是正确的。 2. So far no correct conclusion has arrived at. 到目前为止,还没有得出任何正确的结论。 3. Such casual dress would not be correct for a formal occasion. 这样的便服不宜在正式的场合穿。 4. Correct the errors in the following sentences, if any. 如果下列句子中有错,请改正。', '形容词: correctable 副词: correctly 名词: correctness 过去式: corrected 过去分词: corrected 现在分词: correcting 第三人称单数: corrects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swamp', '[swɑːmp]', 'n.沼泽；湿地；困境 v.淹没；使陷于困境；使忙于应付', '1. In the swamp we were beset by mosquitoes. 我们在沼泽地受到蚊子的围攻。 2. The heavy rain has turned the small garden into a swamp. 大雨使这小花园变成了一块沼泽地。 3. Walk through the swamp and we can see the hunter\'s cabin. 走过这片湿地就能看到猎人的小屋了。 4. Their company is in a financial swamp. 他们的公司陷入了财政困境。 5. In summer visitors swamp the island. 夏天，这个岛上熙熙攘攘，人满为患。', '形容词: swampy 名词: swampiness 过去式: swamped 过去分词: swamped 现在分词: swamping 第三人称单数: swamps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('merit', '[\'merɪt]', 'n.优点；功绩；价值 v.值得；应得', '1. This method at least had the merit of simplicity. 这种办法至少有简单明了的优点。 2. Charms strikes the sight, but merit wins the soul. 美貌吸引目光,优点赢得心灵。 3. That will subtract nothing from his merit. 那将无损于他的功绩。 4. Promotion should be based on merit alone. 晋升应完全根据功绩。 5. His new achievements merit our attention. 他取得的新成就值得关注。', '形容词: meritless 过去式: merited 过去分词: merited 现在分词: meriting 第三人称单数: merits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('profound', '[prə\'faʊnd]', 'adj.深奥的；渊博的；极度的；意义深远的', '1. Beauty is but superficial while mind is profound. 美貌是肤浅的,而思想才是深邃的。 2. I was impressed by his devotion to his research but I didn\'t have the slightest interest in his profound theories. 给我留下了很深印象,但我对他那些深奥的理论丝毫不感兴趣。 3. Our professor is a man of profound learning. 我们的教授是一个学识渊博的人。 4. Reading makes a full man, meditation a profound man, discourse a clear man. 阅读培养学问丰富的人,思考培养见识深刻的人,演讲培养思路清晰的人。', '副词: profoundly 比较级: profounder 最高级: profoundest 名词: profoundness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legacy', '[\'leɡəsi]', 'n.遗赠物；先人或过去遗留下来的东西 adj.[计算机]旧系统的', '1. He left me a small legacy in a nuncupative will, as a token of his kindness to me. 他囗头遗言上遗留给我一点小小遗产作为他对我关爱的表征。 2. These are the cultural legacies of the Renaissance. 这些是文艺复兴时期的文化遗产。', '名词复数: legacies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('melodic', '[mə\'lɑːdɪk]', 'adj.旋律优美的；旋律的', '1. His voice had a rich melodic quality . 他的音色浑厚而优美。 2. It is a very melodic piece with a strong oriental color and style. 这首曲目中有着很浓厚的东方色彩与情调，极富音乐性。 3. I could hear several melodic strands simultaneously. 我可以同时听到几个旋律。 4. Americans have a melodic, jazzy way of producing sounds. 美国人发音很具有旋律性和爵士乐的味道。', '副词: melodically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pleasure', '[\'pleʒər]', 'n.愉快；高兴；快事；（用于回答对方的感谢）荣幸 vt.使高兴 vi.高兴；享受快乐', '1. She took no pleasure in her work. 她觉得自己的工作毫无乐趣。 2. I will remember this meeting with pleasure. 我会愉快地记着这次的会晤。 3. She seemed to take pleasure in our suffering. 她似乎对我们的痛苦幸灾乐祸。 4. It is a pleasure to work with you. 和你一起工作真是件乐事。 5. I really don\'t know how to pleasure him. 我真不知道如何让他高兴。 6. I pleasure in your company. 和你在一起我感到高兴。', '形容词: pleasureless 过去式: pleasured 过去分词: pleasured 现在分词: pleasuring 第三人称单数: pleasures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('censor', '[\'sensər]', 'n.检查员；监察官 vt.检查', '1. They had to accept the blue pencil of the censor. 他们不得不接受检查员的修改。 2. Don\'t write anything that will bother the censor. 你可别写什么给检查员找麻烦的话。 3. A white censor was standing over me. 有一个白人监察官在监视着我。 4. The censor insisted on excising the passage from the film. 电影审查员坚持剪去影片的这一段。 5. It is not constitutional to censor the press. 审查新闻是违反宪法的。', '形容词: censorable 过去式: censored 过去分词: censored 现在分词: censoring 第三人称单数: censors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('terror', '[\'terər]', 'n.恐怖；惊骇；<口>令人惧怕或讨厌的人或事物', '1. Her face worked as she stared at him in terror. 她惊恐地注视着他，脸也吓得抽动起来。 2. She let out a scream of terror. 她发出恐怖的叫喊。 3. His terror is so great that he can do nothing. 他惊骇万分以致什么事都不能做。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compulsory', '[kəm\'pʌlsəri]', 'adj.强制的；势在必行的；义务的', '1. Attendance at evening prayers is not compulsory. 参加晚祷并非硬性规定。 2. I think it is compulsory. 我认为这是非做不可的。 3. The car insurance is compulsory. 这项汽车保险是强制性的。 4. I think it is compulsory to look over the house. 我认为检查这栋房子势在必行。', '副词: compulsorily 名词: compulsoriness 名词复数: compulsories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rotten', '[\'rɑːtn]', 'adj.腐烂的；腐朽的；<口>极坏的；讨厌的 adv.非常', '1. One smell of the rotten meat was enough! 这腐烂的肉闻一下就够受的了。 2. This place has an odious smell; something must be rotten. 这个地方有一股臭味，一定有东西腐烂了。 3. The wood was so rotten that you could put your finger through it. 这木料腐朽了,你可以用手指戳穿它。 4. They are contaminating the minds of our young people with these rotten ideas. 他们正用这些腐朽的思想污染着我们青年人的头脑。 5. The child is spoiled rotten. 这个小孩被宠坏了。', '副词: rottenly 比较级: rottener 最高级: rottenest 名词: rottenness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chorus', '[\'kɔːrəs]', 'n.合唱队；歌舞队；齐声说道；副歌部分 vt.合唱', '1. The audience chimed in on the chorus. 听众开始跟合唱队一起唱起来。 2. The chorus is dressed as fairies. 歌舞队的人都装扮成仙子。 3. When I asked questions, they answered up in chorus. 我提问题时,他们迅速齐声回答。 4. The chorus is very catchy to say the least. 副歌部分很容易上口。 5. The papers all chorused the praises of the President. 各报都异口同声地对总统表示赞扬。', '名词复数: choruses 过去式: chorused/chorussed 过去分词: chorused/chorussed 现在分词: chorusing/chorussing 第三人称单数: choruses/chorusses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instantaneous', '[ˌɪnstən\'teɪniəs]', 'adj.瞬间的；即刻的', '1. Relief was instantaneous. 痛苦的消除是瞬间的事 2. Death is instantaneous in a fatal accident. 在致命的事故中，死亡是即刻发生的。 3. The reaction of the audience was instantaneous. 观众即刻有了反应。 4. He had an instantaneous response. 他立刻作了反应。', '副词: instantaneously 名词: instantaneity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('absurd', '[əb\'sɜːrd]', 'adj.荒唐的；可笑的；不合理的 n.荒唐', '1. He finally recovered from an absurd infatuation. 他终于从荒唐的迷恋中醒悟过来。 2. What an absurd suggestion! 多荒谬的建议啊！ 3. We have no intention of lying down under these absurd allegations. 对这些荒谬的指控我们是不甘受辱的。 4. It was absurd of you to suggest such a thing. 你居然建议这样的事，太可笑了。 5. The proposal borders on the absurd. 该提议近乎可笑。', '副词: absurdly 名词: absurdity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barbecue', '[\'bɑːrbɪkjuː]', 'n.烤肉；烧烤；烤架 v.烤炙', '1. The sunshine bodes well for our barbecue. 明媚的阳光对我们的烤肉野餐是个吉兆。 2. The rain loused up the barbecue. 下雨弄砸了烤肉野餐。 3. If you\'re not busy Sunday, we\'d love to have you both over for a barbecue. 如果你周日有空，我们想请你们俩来吃烧烤。 4. We can\'t calculate on having good weather for the barbecue. 我们不能指望着有好天气才去烧烤。 5. Now and then we like to barbecue chicken in the back yard. 我们偶而会在后院子里烤鸡吃。', '过去式: barbecued 过去分词: barbecued 现在分词: barbecuing 第三人称单数: barbecues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('critique', '[krɪ\'tiːk]', 'n.批评；批评法；评论', '1. He plays down Mr. Brown\'s idea in his critique. 他在自己的评论中大肆批评布朗先生的想法。 2. The book presents a critique of the Government\'s policies. 该书对政府的政策作出了批评性的分析. 3. Most of this critique is familiar enough. 许多此类的批评已经相当为大家熟悉。 4. They all joined in a very spirited critique upon the party. 她们凑在一起对那伙人发表了一通痛快淋漓的批评。', '过去式: critiqued 过去分词: critiqued 现在分词: critiquing 第三人称单数: critiques');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('implicate', '[\'ɪmplɪkeɪt]', 'vt.牵涉；意味着；暗示', '1. His enemies tried to implicate him in the murder. 他的仇人竭力想把他牵扯进谋杀案中。 2. He was deeply implicated in the plot. 他与该阴谋牵涉颇深。 3. His absence implicates disagreement. 他的缺席意味着他不同意。 4. The results implicate poor hygiene as one cause of the outbreak. 这些结果说明卫生条件差是疾病流行的一个原因。', '过去式: implicated 过去分词: implicated 现在分词: implicating 第三人称单数: implicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diverse', '[daɪ\'vɜːrs]', 'adj.不同的；多种多样的', '1. They are the people from diverse cultures. 他们是些有着不同文化背景的人。 2. Since then，she has played a diverse range of roles. 从那时起,她出演了各种不同的角色。 3. Her interests are very diverse. 她的兴趣非常广泛。 4. Their way of life is rich, diverse and rooted. 他们的生活方式丰富多彩,多种多样,扎根传统。', '副词: diversely 名词: diverseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('addict', '[\'ædɪkt]', 'vt.沉溺；使 ... 上瘾 n.耽溺者；上瘾者', '1. The young generation should addict themselves to science. 年轻的一代应该酷爱科学。 2. His tastes addict him to the study of antiquity. 嗜好使他沉迷于研究古代的事物。 3. He was addicted to cocaine. 他吸可卡因上瘾。 4. He is turning into an internet addict. 他快变成网虫了。', '形容词: addictive 过去式: addicted 过去分词: addicted 现在分词: addicting 第三人称单数: addicts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hesitate', '[\'hezɪteɪt]', 'vi.犹豫；不情愿；口吃', '1. Do not hesitate to tell us if you have a problem . 你有问题就直截了当地告诉我们。 2. I would hesitate to get involved in this adventure. 我犹豫是否参加这次探险。 3. She hesitated to hurt the child\'s feelings. 她不想伤害孩子的感情。 4. I hesitate to spend so much money on clothes. 我舍不得把这麽多钱花在穿衣服上.', '副词: hesitatingly 名词: hesitation 过去式: hesitated 过去分词: hesitated 现在分词: hesitating 第三人称单数: hesitates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abhor', '[əb\'hɔːr]', 'vt.憎恶；厌恶；痛恨', '1. They abhor all forms of racial discrimination. 他们憎恶任何形式的种族歧视。 2. Most people abhor cruelyt to children. 大部分人憎恶虐待儿童。 3. I abhor every commonplace phrase by which wit is intended. 我厌恶所有那些力图表现智慧的陈腐不堪的俗话。 4. I will put my dwelling place among you, and I will not abhor you. 我要在你们中间立我的帐幕，我的心也不厌恶你们。', '名词: abhorrer 过去式: abhorred 过去分词: abhorred 现在分词: abhorring 第三人称单数: abhors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('neoclassical', '[ˌniːoʊ\'klæsɪkl]', 'adj.新古典主义的 =neoclassic.', '1. The house is decorated in neoclassical style. 这座房子装修为新古典主义风格。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bias', '[\'baɪəs]', 'n.偏见；偏爱；斜纹 vt.使偏心', '1. He has a bias against Japanese products. 他讨厌日本的产品。 2. Histories are often warped by bias. 历史常为偏见所曲解。 3. The judge dispenses the law without bias. 这名法官执法公正无私。 4. Her scientific bias showed itself in early childhood. 她在科学方面的倾向性在孩童时代就已显现出来。 5. The lawyer made a tearful plea to bias the jury. 这名律师以哭诉影响陪审团的裁决。', '过去式: biased/biassed 过去分词: biased/biassed 现在分词: biasing/biassing 第三人称单数: biases/biasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('endow', '[ɪn\'daʊ]', 'vt.捐助；赋予；使具有某种品质', '1. I can only endow 100 dollors at most. 我充其量只能捐助100美元。 2. He endowed the hospital with a large fortune. 他捐赠一笔巨款给这家医院。 3. She both built and endowed the hospital. 她不仅建了医院还给医院捐赠资金。 4. He is endowed with literary talent. 他有文学天分。', '过去式: endowed 过去分词: endowed 现在分词: endowing 第三人称单数: endows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disadvantage', '[ˌdɪsəd\'væntɪdʒ]', 'n.不利；不利条件；损害；损失', '1. The situation put us at a serious disadvantage. 形势使我们处于非常不利的地位。 2. If you don\'t speak good English, you\'ll be at a big disadvantage when you try to get a job. 你要是英语讲得不好，找工作时就会处于非常不利的地位。 3. The system puts the firm at a disadvantage because of its overmuch manpower. 由于过剩的人力，这一体制使公司处境不利。 4. My lack of practical experience was a disadvantage. 我缺少实际经验是个不利条件。', '过去式: disadvantaged 过去分词: disadvantaged 现在分词: disadvantaging 第三人称单数: disadvantages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adjoining', '[ə\'dʒɔɪnɪŋ]', 'adj.毗邻的 动词adjoin的现在分词.', '1. Flames burned out two adjoining houses. 大火把附近两栋房子烧掉了。 2. We heard laughter in the adjoining room. 我们听到了邻屋的笑声。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spray', '[spreɪ]', 'v.喷雾；喷射；扫射 n.喷雾；喷雾器；水沫', '1. He sprayed paint on the wall. 他把漆喷在墙上。 2. We should spray some hairspray on your hair. 我们应该喷些发胶在你的头发上。 3. Please spray some water on the flower. 请给花洒些水。 4. The gangsters sprayed the car with machinegun bullets. 匪徒们用机枪狂扫汽车。 5. I\'ve lost my throat spray. 我的润喉剂喷筒丢了。', '名词: sprayer 过去式: sprayed 过去分词: sprayed 现在分词: spraying 第三人称单数: sprays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repertory', '[\'repərtɔːri]', 'n.全部剧目；仓库；积贮', '1. She acted with a repertory company for three years. 她在一个轮演剧目剧团里演出三年。 2. Jane weighed down her repertory with these plays. 简加上这几出戏，使她的演出剧目得到了加强。 3. It is up to each company to decide its own repertory. 我们的常备剧目基本由每个剧团决定。', '形容词: repertorial 名词复数: repertories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forlorn', '[fər\'lɔːrn]', 'adj.孤独的；凄凉的；渺茫的', '1. She had a forlorn look on her face. 她脸上有一种孤独的神情。 2. She looked wretched and forlorn, despairing of the arrival of a friend who had promised to meet her. 她看上去又可怜又孤独，对于答应来看她的朋友的到来已不抱希望。 3. The house stood forlorn and empty. 房子被弃置了，空无一物。 4. He made his final forlorn attempt. 他做了最后一次几乎无望的努力。', '副词: forlornly 名词: forlornness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('platitude', '[\'plætɪtuːd]', 'n.陈词滥调；平凡；陈腐', '1. It was a platitude to maintain the fiction that he was conferring a great boon on me. 这是一种陈腐的老生常谈，旨在维护似乎他给了我极大恩惠的假象。', '形容词: platitudinous 副词: platitudinously');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deceive', '[dɪ\'siːv]', 'vt.欺骗 vi.行骗', '1. It\'s not honorable to deceive them. 欺骗他们是不光彩的。 2. He was foiled in his attempt to deceive us. 他企图欺骗我们,但没有得逞。 3. He deceived me into signing the papers. 他骗我在文件上签了字。 4. You are deceiving yourself if you still believe that she loves you. 你如果还相信她爱你，你就是在欺骗自己。 5. Appearances can deceive. 外表是有欺骗性的。', '形容词: deceivable 副词: deceivingly 名词: deceiver 过去式: deceived 过去分词: deceived 现在分词: deceiving 第三人称单数: deceives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('limestone', '[\'laɪmstoʊn]', 'n.石灰石', '1. Caves form when water infiltrates limestone. 水渗透石灰石则形成洞穴。 2. We may burn limestone to obtain lime. 我们可以通过烧石灰石来得到石灰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clam', '[klæm]', 'n.蛤；沉默寡言的人 vi.保持沉默；挖蚌', '1. Yup! I also like clam soup and sea cucumbers. 对呀！我还喜欢蛤仔汤和海参。 2. Everybody shut up like a clam as soon as you mention it. 你一提及此事，大家便都闭口不言 3. He is a clam about his business dealing. 他对自己的生意买卖守口如瓶。 4. It started off well, but he seemed to clam up towards the end. 刚开始很，但是最后他似乎有些沉默。', '名词: clammer 过去式: clammed 过去分词: clammed 现在分词: clamming 第三人称单数: clams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perennial', '[pə\'reniəl]', 'adj.永久的；反复出现的；多年生的 n.多年生植物', '1. Politics provides a perennial subject for argument. 政治是一种长期争论不休的话题。 2. Our perennial problem is not having enough money. 长期困扰我们的问题就是缺钱。 3. The dandelion is a perennial plant. 该蒲公英是一种多年生的植物。 4. A galaxy is an evergreen perennial. 加莱克斯草是一种多年生常绿植物。', '副词: perennially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('establish', '[ɪ\'stæblɪʃ]', 'v.建立；确立；创办；安顿', '1. We have established trade ties with these regions. 我们和这些地区建立了贸易关系。 2. There is an urgent need to establish a strict responsibility system. 急需建立严格的责任制度。 3. He has established his theory. 他确立了他的学说。 4. The framework of a social security system was established by and large. 社会保障体系框架基本确立。', '名词: establisher 过去式: established 过去分词: established 现在分词: establishing 第三人称单数: establishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mostly', '[\'moʊstli]', 'adv.主要地；通常', '1. Recycled materials are mostly of limited use. 再生材料大多用途有限。 2. He reads the occasional book, but mostly just magazines. 他偶尔也看书，但大多只看杂志。 3. Lizards live mostly in warm climates. 蜥蜴主要生长在气候温暖的地方。 4. He works mostly in London office. 他通常在伦敦办事处工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('startle', '[\'stɑːrtl]', 'v.（使）吃惊；（使）惊愕 n.吃惊；惊恐', '1. He was startled by the news. 这消息使他大吃一惊。 2. He startled from sleep. 他从睡梦中惊醒起来。 3. The least noise would startle the timid child. 最小的响声也会吓着这个胆小的孩子的。 4. Let\'s hide ourselves behind the door and startle her. 藏在门后面，咱们吓她一下。 5. He gave me a startle. 他吓了我一跳。', '副词: startlingly 名词: startlingness 过去式: startled 过去分词: startled 现在分词: startling 第三人称单数: startles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('secretion', '[sɪ\'kriːʃn]', 'n.分泌；分泌物；藏匿', '1. Saliva is secretion of the salivary glands. 唾液是唾液腺的分泌物。 2. The secretion of bile is useful for our bodies. 胆汁的分泌对我们的身体很有用处。 3. Is there much secretion from your eyes? 眼里的分泌物多吗?', '形容词: secretionary');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('carnivore', '[\'kɑːrnɪvɔːr]', 'n.食肉动物；食虫植物', '1. Lions and tigers are carnivores. 狮子和老虎是食肉动物。 2. I did mostly vegetarian food but put a couple of meat dishes out for the carnivores. 我基本上吃素，但是我会给吃肉的人准备一些肉食。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('firm', '[fɜːrm]', 'n.公司；商行 adj.坚定的；结实的；坚固的；严格的 v.(使)变得坚实；确定 adv.稳固地；坚定地', '1. He has established his own firm. 他已建立起自己的公司。 2. He resigned his directorship and left the firm. 他放弃了董事职务, 离开了公司。 3. The businessment started out as an errand boy at the age of 14 in a firm. 这位大企业家从14岁时起就在一家商行里当听差。 4. We must maintain a firm attitude. 我们必须采取坚定的态度。 5. Exercise will firm up your muscles. 锻炼身体能使肌肉结实。 6. They made a firm pledge to support us. 他们做出了坚定地承诺支持我们。', '副词: firmly 比较级: firmer 最高级: firmest 名词: firmness 过去式: firmed 过去分词: firmed 现在分词: firming 第三人称单数: firms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avalanche', '[\'ævəlæntʃ]', 'n.雪崩；大量 v.雪崩', '1. The avalanche whelmed the small mountain village. 雪崩淹没了小山村。 2. Three climbers are safe after the avalanche. 雪崩过后，三个登山者平安无事。 3. He was buried by an avalanche and had to be dug out. 他遇雪崩被埋住了，得把他挖出来。 4. What a precarious situation we were in when the avalanche started! 雪崩发生的时候我们的处境多么危险啊！ 5. Higher still the snow was ready to avalanche. 在更高处积雪随时都会崩塌。', '过去式: avalanched 过去分词: avalanched 现在分词: avalanching 第三人称单数: avalanches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('odd', '[ɑːd]', 'adj.奇数的；古怪的；零散的；剩余的', '1. 1,3, 5 and 7 are odd numbers. 1,3, 5 和 7 是奇数。 2. Graphs are on even pages and tables are on odd pages. 图在偶数页,表格在奇数页。 3. It\'s very odd that she didn\'t reply to our letter. 她没有回我们的信是件很奇怪的事。 4. On the way, one can watch pines in all kinds of odd shapes. 一路上,人们可以观赏到各种各样形态怪异的松树。', '副词: oddly 比较级: odder 最高级: oddest 名词: oddness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mast', '[mæst]', 'n.船桅；旗杆；天线杆 abbr.磁性环形激波管(风洞研究用)(=Magnetic Annular Shock Tube)', '1. The mast went by the board in the storm. 那船桅在暴风雨中落于船外。 2. We heared the flaps of the sail against the mast. 我们听见帆拍击着船桅的声音。 3. Flags were flying on every mast. 旗帜在每根旗杆上飘扬。 4. The flag was riding up the mast. 旗帜飘荡着升上旗杆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skeletal', '[\'skelətl]', 'adj.骨骼的；梗概的；骸骨的', '1. These foods replenish the skeletal needs of the body. 这些食物补充身体骨骼的需要。 2. He has written only a skeletal plot for the book so far. 那本书他目前只写了一个情节梗概。', '副词: skeletally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intersection', '[ˌɪntər\'sekʃn]', 'n.交集；十字路口；交叉点', '1. The basic algorithm for arriving at the final, applicable set of permissions is to compute the intersection of all. 最后得到的一组适用权限的算法是要计算所有权限的交集。 2. Do not use multiple aliases for a single table in the same query to simulate index intersection. 不要在同一查询中为一个表使用多个别名来模拟索引交集。 3. Breastworks were thrown up at major intersections. 在主要的十字路口都匆匆筑起了胸墙。 4. Cut to the left at the next intersection. 在下一个十字路口向左急转', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('portion', '[\'pɔːrʃn]', 'n.部分；命运；分担的责任；份 v.分配；命运注定', '1. I read a portion of the manuscript. 我读了原稿的一部分。 2. The cake is big enough to be divided into sixteen portions. 这个蛋糕很大,足够分为十六份。 3. He has accepted his portion in life. 他安于天命。 4. Sorrow has always been her portion. 她的命运一直与悲哀相连。', '形容词: portionable 名词: portioner 过去式: portioned 过去分词: portioned 现在分词: portioning 第三人称单数: portions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('downhearted', '[ˌdaʊn\'hɑːrtɪd]', 'adj.消沉的；沮丧的', '1. Downhearted thoughts hinder progress. 消沉的思想妨碍进步。 2. I have not become downhearted or low-spirited 我并没有灰心或消沉。 3. Don\'t be downhearted! 别心灰意冷！ 4. He is very downhearted about the poor grade he got in school. 他对糟糕的学业成绩感到十分沮丧。', '副词: downheartedly 名词: downheartedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scorch', '[skɔːrtʃ]', 'v.（使）烧焦；变焦；（使）枯萎 n.烧焦', '1. Jenny scorch her jacket carelessly while she is smoking her pipe. 珍妮抽烟斗时不小心把夹克烧焦。 2. Luckily, flashes of such strong radiation occur so far away they will not scorch our planet. 幸运的是，诸如这类的强辐射大发生离我们非常的遥远，他们不会烧焦我们的地球。 3. Jenny scorch her jacket carelessly while she is smoking her pipe. 珍妮抽烟斗时不小心把夹克烧焦。 4. Luckily, flashes of such strong radiation occur so far away they will not scorch our planet. 幸运的是，诸如这类的强辐射大发生离我们非常的遥远，他们不会烧焦我们的地球。', '副词: scorchingly 过去式: scorched 过去分词: scorched 现在分词: scorching 第三人称单数: scorches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assassin', '[ə\'sæsn]', 'n.暗杀者；刺客 Assassin. n.暗杀基督教十字军成员的穆斯林狂热派', '1. He is a cruel assassin. 他是个残忍的杀手。 2. The assassin was wanted by the police nationwide. 那个暗杀者被警方的全国通缉。 3. He fell a victim to the dagger of the assassin. 他死于刺客的匕首之下。 4. He hired an assassin to kill his competitor. 他雇用了一名刺客去暗杀他的竞争者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irresolute', '[ɪ\'rezəluːt]', 'adj.优柔寡断的；踌躇不定的；无决断的', '1. Irresolute persons make poor leaders. 优柔寡断的人不会成为好领袖。', '副词: irresolutely 名词: irresoluteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trench', '[trentʃ]', 'n.沟；沟渠；战壕 v.挖沟；侵占', '1. The farmers gouged out a trench across the field. 农民们挖了一条穿过田野的沟。 2. They dig trench to keep the forest fire from spread. 他们挖沟以阻止森林大火蔓延。 3. I forgot to dig a trench around the tent. 我忘了在帐篷四周挖一条沟。 4. They toiled all day digging the trench. 他们整天艰苦地挖壕沟。 5. The troops received orders to trench the outpost. 部队接到命令在前哨周围筑壕加强防卫。', '过去式: trenched 过去分词: trenched 现在分词: trenching 第三人称单数: trenches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stellar', '[\'stelər]', 'adj.星(状的)；和电影明星有关的；主要的；一流的', '1. Collisions between the gas clouds may trigger a stellar baby boom. 气体云之间的碰撞可能会触发产星高潮。 2. Now an international team of astronomers says you can blame gusts of stellar wind. 现在一个国际天文学团队说，原因在于猛烈的星风。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constricted', '[kənˈstrɪktɪd]', 'adj.狭窄的；收缩的 动词constrict的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Another application migth be non-surgical cardiac bypasses that grow new blood vessels around those blocked or constricted by atherosclerosis. 另一个应用可能是建立非手术心脏旁路，生成新的血管围绕这些由于动脉粥样硬化阻塞或狭窄的血管。 2. As the stress approaches that of the tensile strength, a material that has begun to flow forms a narrow, constricted region that is easily fractured. 随著应力接近抗张强度，开始流动的材料会形成一个狭窄的收缩区，很容易发生断裂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pendant', '[\'pendənt]', 'n.垂饰；悬挂物 adj.下垂的；悬而未决的（=pendent）', '1. It looked so grand that when Rube asked me again if she could try my jewels on just for a minute, I offered her the pendant. 这儿太气派了，以至于鲁布再次求我能不能让她只戴一分钟我的首饰时，我把有垂饰的项链给了她。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hind', '[haɪnd]', 'adj.后部的；在后的 n.雌鹿；石斑鱼', '1. The hind leg of this horse was broken. 这匹马的后腿断了。 2. The dog was sitting on his hind legs. 那只狗用它的后腿端坐着。', '异体字: hinder');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('partially', '[\'pɑːrʃəli]', 'adv.部分地；不公平地', '1. He was only partially to blame for the accident. 他对事故只应负部分责任。 2. The new theory has been partially corroborated. 这个新的理论已部分地被证实。 3. She loved her son Tom only partially. 她偏爱她的儿子汤姆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('design', '[dɪ\'zaɪn]', 'n.设计；图样；图案；目的 v.设计；计划', '1. This dress is of the latest design. 这件衣服是最新设计。 2. He chalked out a design on the blackboard. 他用粉笔在黑板上勾划出一个图样。 3. The bedcover was quilted in a flower design. 床罩被缝成花卉图案。 4. His evil designs were frustrated. 他的罪恶企图未能得逞。 5. He designed us a beautiful house. 他为我们设计了一所很美的房子。', '形容词: designable 过去式: designed 过去分词: designed 现在分词: designing 第三人称单数: designs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nitrogen', '[\'naɪtrədʒən]', 'n.氮', '1. Air consists chiefly of nitrogen. 空气主要由氮气组成。 2. The lamp is full of gaseous nitrogen. 灯里充满了气体氮。 3. Nitrogen is a gas without colour or smell. 氮是一种无色无臭的气体。 4. Nitrogen forms most of the Earth\'s air. 地球上空气的大部分成分是氮气。', '形容词: nitrogenous 简写符号: N');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('taunt', '[tɔːnt]', 'n.辱骂；嘲弄 v.嘲弄', '1. His genial sufficiency was a taunt and a mockery to many. 他那么和蔼自满的态度，许多人都认为是一种辱骂和嘲弄。 2. But in England if the palm faces inward it\'s a taunt, especially if executed with an up-ward jerk of the fingers. 可在英国，做该手势时如果掌心向内，特别是还同时把手指往上伸的话，则表示对人的辱骂。 3. He will taunt an opponent endlessly, even during battle, raising their ire until they make a fatal mistake - and then take advantage of them. 即使在战斗中，他也会无休止的嘲弄对手，激起他们的怒气直到他们犯下致命错误，然后他就会取得优势。', '副词: tauntingly 名词: taunter 过去式: taunted 过去分词: taunted 现在分词: taunting 第三人称单数: taunts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('moisture', '[\'mɔɪstʃər]', 'n.水分；潮气；湿度', '1. The plants absorb moisture from the soil. 植物从土壤中吸取水分。 2. The sun will take the moisture out of the clothes. 太阳光会把衣服上的水分蒸发掉。 3. If you air your quilt on such a wet day, it\'ll soak up the moisture. 如果在这么潮湿的天晒被子，被子就会把湿气都吸去。 4. Amounts of moisture in soil vary greatly. 土壤中湿度变化很大。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inevitably', '[ɪn\'evɪtəbli]', 'adv.不可避免地', '1. The decision will inevitably cut both ways. 这个决定不可避免地产生两种结果。 2. Inevitably he failed the exam, because he was lazy. 因为他很懒惰,考试当然不及格。 3. Speakers who ramble are almost inevitably bores. 信口开河的演说家几乎是不可避免地要讨人嫌恶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('weathering', '[\'weðərɪŋ]', 'n.风化 动词weather的现在分词形式.', '1. The rock is resistant to weathering and erosion. 这种岩石不易风化和侵蚀。 2. Weathering makes possible the sorting of rock materials. 风化使岩石物质有可能进行分选。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compromise', '[\'kɑːmprəmaɪz]', 'n.妥协；折衷；折衷案；和解 vt.妥协处理；危害 vi.妥协，和解；让步', '1. He did it without compromise of his dignity. 他做这事而不损及他的尊严。 2. The agreement is a compromise, not a sell-out. 这个协议是双方妥协的产物而不是一方让步。 3. After some discussion we arrive at a compromise. 经过一番讨论之后，我们达成一项折衷方案。 4. Or are we ready to compromise our faith? 或者，我们准备好了在信仰上折衷吗？ 5. With this increased awareness, attackers are finding it more difficult to compromise systems at the network level. 由于对这些认识得越来越清楚，攻击者发现在网络级上危害系统更加困难。 6. They found it wiser to compromise with her. 他们觉得与她妥协更明智。', '名词: compromiser 过去式: compromised 过去分词: compromised 现在分词: compromising 第三人称单数: compromises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('multiple', '[\'mʌltɪpl]', 'adj.多种多样的；许多的 n.倍数；并联', '1. He is the person with multiple injuries. 他就是那个多处受伤的人。 2. A multiple crash can often be seen on that motorway. 那条公路上的联环撞车事故很多。 3. Words can have multiple meanings. 词汇可以有许多释义。 4. 10 is a multiple of 5. 10是5的倍数。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frustrate', '[\'frʌstreɪt]', 'vt.挫败；击败；使沮丧；使灰心 adj.无益的；挫败的；挫折的', '1. This is the place that we frustrate enemy. 这是我们挫败敌人的地方。 2. They made their preparations to frustrate the conspiracy. 他们作好准备挫败以这个阴谋。 3. The terrible weather frustrated our hopes of going out. 恶劣的天气使我们外出的愿望无法实现。 4. We have the confidence in frustrating our enemy. 我们有信心击败敌人。 5. The prisoner made a frustrate attempt to escape. 囚犯妄图逃跑。', '副词: frustratingly 名词: frustrater 过去式: frustrated 过去分词: frustrated 现在分词: frustrating 第三人称单数: frustrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oxide', '[\'ɑːksaɪd]', 'n.氧化物', '1. The nitride on oxide layers remains intact. 氧化物表层上面的氮化物保持原状不动。 2. Oxide is usually seen in our daily life. 在我们的日常生活中氧化物很常见。', '形容词: oxidic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('questionnaire', '[ˌkwestʃə\'ner]', 'n.调查表；问卷', '1. We gave them some questionnaires for collecting data. 为了收集数据我们发给他们一些调查表。 2. Please fill up the blanks in the questionnaire. 请把调查表填写一下。 3. Please complete and return the enclosed questionnaire. 所附问卷请填妥交回。 4. Is a questionnaire answered by 500 people truly representative of national opinion? 一份调查问卷有500人作答,是否能真正代表全国人民的意见?', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gabble', '[\'ɡæbl]', 'v.急促而不清楚地说；喋喋不休地讲 n.急促讲出而叫人听不清说的话', '1. Don\'t gabble, Lucy, I can\'t understand when you run your words together. 不要说得那么急，露西，你说话象连珠炮似的，我听不懂。 2. She was nervous and started to gabble. 她紧张得话都说不清了。 3. In the end, I couldn\'t bear her gabble any more. 最后，我终于受不了她的罗嗦了。 4. Who is speaking at such a gabble ? 谁在说话说得那么急，叫人听不清楚?', '名词: gabbler 过去式: gabbled 过去分词: gabbled 现在分词: gabbling 第三人称单数: gabbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cower', '[\'kaʊər]', 'v.畏缩；退缩；抖缩', '1. The dog cowered (down) under the table. 那只狗吓得蜷伏在桌子底下。 2. In face of difficulties, we should not cower but meet them bravely. 面临困难时我们不应该退缩，而应该勇敢地面对。 3. He cowered away/back as she raised her hand to hit him. 她扬手打他,他立即退缩开[向后退缩]。', '过去式: cowered 过去分词: cowered 现在分词: cowering 第三人称单数: cowers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scavenger', '[\'skævɪndʒər]', 'n.拾荒者；食腐动物；清除剂', '1. He\'s just fit for a job as scavenger. 他只配当个清道夫。 2. The shark is usually a scavenger rather than a hunter. 鲨鱼通常是一个清道夫，而不是一个猎人。 3. Proanthocyanidin is a effective natural free radical scavenger. 原花青素是一种天然有效的自由基清除剂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cordial', '[\'kɔːrdʒəl]', 'n.兴奋剂；补品 adj.热忱的；诚恳的；兴奋的', '1. By means of a few drops of strong cordial, the doctor revived the besotted corpse for a few minutes. 博士滴了几滴强烈的兴奋剂，使这个没有知觉的身躯复活了几分钟。 2. It was a cordial affair in which Pancalli expressed his appreciation for the work carried out by Juventus in recent months. 这是一次热忱的会晤，潘卡利感谢了近几个月来尤文所做的工作。 3. Please accept my cordial and humblest apologies. 请接受我诚恳的道歉。', '副词: cordially 名词: cordiality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dealer', '[\'diːlər]', 'n.商人；经销商；发牌者；毒品贩子', '1. The dealer was slavering over some precious stones. 那商人对一些宝石垂涎欲滴。 2. She beat the dealer down to a much better price. 她跟商人杀到一个很合适的价位。 3. The book dealer would not break the set. 这个图书经销商不会打破规定。 4. The dealer was shuffling the cards. 发牌者正在洗牌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conservatory', '[kən\'sɜːrvətɔːri]', 'n.温室；音乐学院', '1. On Sunday, he provided a picnic brunch in Central Park\'s Conservatory Garden. 周日，他在中央公园的温室花园搞野餐活动。 2. The conservatory must be protected! 温室必须被保护！ 3. He learned to bel canto in a conservatory. 他在音乐学院学习的是美声唱法。 4. One does not learn to straddle a cello that way at a conservatory. 音乐学院是不会教人这样骑着大提琴演奏的。', '名词复数: conservatories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('habitually', '[hə\'bɪtʃuəli]', 'adv.日常地；习惯地', '1. A person who uncritically or habitually conforms to the customs, rules, or styles of a group. 墨守陈规者毫无抗议的或习惯性的遵循习俗、规则或某组织规范的人 2. One who habitually smokes marijuana. 吸大麻者习惯性吸食大麻者 3. One who habitually takes advantage of the generosity of others without making any useful return. 寄生虫总是利用别人的慷慨大方而从不做任何有益回报的人', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vacuum', '[\'vækjuəm]', 'n.真空；真空吸尘器；空白 adj.产生（利用）真空的 v.用吸尘器打扫', '1. The food is kept in the absolute vacuum. 这食物保存在绝对真空中。 2. I bought a vacuum yesterday. 昨天我买了个真空吸尘器。 3. His wife\'s death left him a vacuum in his life. 他妻子的去世使他的生活变得空虚。 4. These\'re vacuum controls. 这是些真空控制装置。 5. Please vacuum the carpets after the breakfast. 早饭后请用吸尘器清扫下地毯。', '名词复数: vacuums 过去式: vacuumed 过去分词: vacuumed 现在分词: vacuuming 第三人称单数: vacuumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laureate', '[\'lɔːriət]', 'n.桂冠诗人；得奖人', '1. He was awarded the poet laureate by the queen. 他被女王封为桂冠诗人。 2. We won a laureate cup. 我们赢得了荣誉奖杯。 3. He was a Nobel laureate in physics. 他是一位诺贝尔物理学奖获得者。', '名词: laureateship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jaw', '[dʒɔː]', 'n.颚；颌；下巴；钳口；说教 v.喋喋不休；教训', '1. A strong square jaw is a sign of firm character. 强健的方颚是性格坚定的象征。 2. He fell from a ladder, and broke his jaw bone. 他从梯子上掉了下来，摔伤了颌骨。 3. Give him a sock on the jaw! 给他下巴上来一拳！ 4. On hearing the news, his jaw dropped. 听到这个消息，他惊讶得张口结舌。 5. Whenever my wife and her mother get together they jaw away for hours. 每当我妻子和她母亲相聚时，她们总要聊上数小时。', '形容词: jawless 过去式: jawed 过去分词: jawed 现在分词: jawing 第三人称单数: jaws');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('define', '[dɪ\'faɪn]', 'v.规定；限定；定义；解释', '1. We should clearly define the scope of our research. 我们应该明确规定我们的研究范围。 2. The bank needs to define and delegate the responsibilities related to the various aspects of its marketing programme. 银行必须规定并授予与营销计划有关的各项职权。 3. The dependent claim shall,by additional technical features,further define the claim which it refers to. 从属权利要求应当用附加的技术特征，对引用的权利要求作进一步限定。 4. The section defines the extent of application of the Act. 该条款用来限定该法令的适用范围。', '形容词: definable 副词: definably 名词: definability 过去式: defined 过去分词: defined 现在分词: defining 第三人称单数: defines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('posit', '[\'pɑːzɪt]', 'v.假定 v.安置', '1. Most religions posit the existence of life after death. 大多数宗教都假定人死后生命仍存在。', '过去式: posited 过去分词: posited 现在分词: positing 第三人称单数: posits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discern', '[dɪ\'sɜːrn]', 'v.辨别；看出；察觉', '1. Sometimes it\'s not easy to discern between the true and the false. 有时辨别真伪并不容易。 2. He was just able to discern the road in the dark. 他在黑暗中勉强能辨出道路。 3. They can discern me in spite of the fog. 虽然有雾，但他们能认得出我。 4. I soon discerned that the man was lying. 我马上察觉出那人在撒谎。', '名词: discerner 过去式: discerned 过去分词: discerned 现在分词: discerning 第三人称单数: discerns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affectionate', '[ə\'fekʃənət]', 'adj.充满感情的；示爱的', '1. He gave her knee an affectionate pat/He gave her an affectionate pat on the knee. 他深情地拍了一下她的膝盖。 2. She gave her mother an affectionate hug. 她紧紧拥抱著她的母亲。 3. He enfolded the child in an affectionate embrace. 他疼爱得把孩子紧紧搂在怀里。 4. She tried to be an affectionate wife. 她试图做个温柔体贴的妻子。', '副词: affectionately 名词: affectionateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('formulate', '[\'fɔːrmjuleɪt]', 'v.用公式表示；系统地阐述；规划；制订', '1. Survey the material first to get a sense of it: formulate some questions. 考查原始材料首先要了解它的意义：用公式解答问题。 2. He formulated his thought clearly. 他清楚确切地表达了自己的思想。 3. He struggled to formulate an answer. 他努力字斟句酌地回答。 4. He thought it time to formulate some plan of action. 他认为这是该筹划一些行动计划的时候了。', '名词: formulation 过去式: formulated 过去分词: formulated 现在分词: formulating 第三人称单数: formulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('specialized', '[\'speʃəlaɪzd]', 'adj.专门的；专科的 动词specialize的过去式和过去分词.', '1. Both games require strength and specialized skills. 两者都要求力量强度和专门的运动技巧。 2. How much experience does he bring to this specialized work? 他使用了多少经验来干这项专业工作？ 3. Specialized knowledge is sometimes more valuable than general knowledge. 专科知识有时比常识更有价值。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('caustic', '[\'kɔːstɪk]', 'adj.腐蚀性的；刻薄的；[物]焦散的 n.腐蚀物；[物]焦散曲面', '1. He opened his mouth to make a caustic retort. 他张嘴开始进行刻薄的反击。 2. The caustic remark dented her ego. 那种尖利刻薄的话语伤害了她的自尊心。', '副词: caustically 名词: causticity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barometer', '[bə\'rɑːmɪtər]', 'n.气压计；晴雨表', '1. Air pressure is measured by a barometer. 空气压力用气压计度量。 2. The barometer began to fall. 气压计的读数开始下降。 3. Hair is a barometer of your general health. 头发是你基本健康状况的晴雨表。 4. Now the barometer points to rain. 晴雨表正显示会下雨。', '形容词: barometric 副词: barometrically 名词: barometry');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('purchase', '[\'pɜːrtʃəs]', 'vt.购买 n.购买；购买的物品', '1. She purchased a number of shares in the company. 她在公司里买了一些股票。 2. Tickets must be purchased two weeks in advance. 票必须提前两周买。 3. The receipt is your proof of purchase. 这张发票是你购物的凭据. 4. The house is the most expensive purchase I have ever made. 房子是我买过的最贵的东西。', '名词: purchaser 过去式: purchased 过去分词: purchased 现在分词: purchasing 第三人称单数: purchases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ability', '[ə\'bɪləti]', 'n.能力；才能', '1. This is a task well within your ability. 这完全是你力所能及的工作。 2. She has the ability to keep calm in an emergency. 她有处变不惊的本事。 3. He is a man of great executive ability. 他是个具有极高管理才能的人。 4. The boy shows remarkable ability at math. 这男孩显示出非凡的数学才能。', '名词复数: abilities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sullen', '[\'sʌlən]', 'adj.愠怒的；闷闷不乐的；阴沉的', '1. The sullen child refused to answer my questions. 那愠怒的孩子拒绝回答我的问题。 2. She had not come to him today with this feeling of sullen antagonism. 她今天并没有带着这种愠怒的抵触情绪到他这儿来。 3. A sullen look shaded his face. 闷闷不乐的表情使他的脸蒙上阴影。 4. This sullen weather disagrees with me. 遇上这种阴沉的天气我就感到不舒服。', '副词: sullenly 比较级: sullener 最高级: sullenest 名词: sullenness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('leap', '[liːp]', 'v.跳跃；跃过；跃 n.跳跃；跃', '1. I leap for joy at the good news. 我一听到这个好消息高兴得跳了起来。 2. The thief leaped the wall and ran away. 小偷越墙逃跑了。 3. His name leapt out at me from the newspaper. 报纸上他的名字一下子跳入我的眼帘。 4. The boy took a leap from the window. 那个男孩从窗口跳下去。', '名词: leaper 过去式: leaped/leapt 过去分词: leaped/leapt 现在分词: leaping 第三人称单数: leaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('configuration', '[kənˌfɪɡjə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.结构；布局；形态；格式塔心理完形 [计算机] 配置.', '1. It is something resembling this structure in configuration or pattern. 这是一种在外形或结构上类似这种构造的东西。 2. The configuration of this plant is complex. 这个工厂的布局很复杂。 3. This is the configuration of the earth\'s surface. 这就是地球表面的形状。 4. Where do I put my configuration files? 我把配置文件放在哪里了?', '形容词: configurative 副词: configurationally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('industry', '[\'ɪndəstri]', 'n.工业；产业；行业；勤勉；勤劳', '1. Since the advent of atomic power, there have been great changes in industry. 自从原子动力问世以后，工业发生了巨大的变化。 2. The tourist trade has become a real industry. 旅游业已经成为真正的产业。 3. The information industry is an infant industry in our country. 信息产业在我国是新兴产业。 4. He wants to widen his knowledge of the industry. 他想扩充自己在这一行业的知识。', '名词复数: industries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corpse', '[kɔːrps]', 'n.尸体', '1. The corpse was laid out by the undertaker. 承办殡葬者准备埋葬尸体。 2. The corpse lies face down in a pool of blood. 尸体俯卧在血泊中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alphabet', '[\'ælfəbet]', 'n.字母表；基本原理(元素)；符号系统', '1. C comes after B in the alphabet. 在字母表中C接在B后面。 2. There are 26 letters in the English alphabet. 英语字母表中有26个字母。 3. The first letter in the English Alphabet is A. 英语字母表中的第一个字母是A。 4. he said the space is the most important character in the alphabet. 他说空格是系统符号里最重要的字符。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oak', '[oʊk]', 'n.橡树；橡木', '1. The birds nested in the oak tree. 鸟在橡树上筑巢。 2. Pine wood saws more easily than oak. 松树要比橡树容易锯。 3. The wine is left to mature in oak barrels. 葡萄酒在橡木桶中陈酿。 4. There was a triptych of pale oak. 有一个浅灰色的三联橡木雕刻。', '形容词: oaken');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lament', '[lə\'ment]', 'n.悲叹；悼词 v.哀悼；惋惜；悲叹', '1. It is the lament of an impoverished peasant. 它是一个已贫穷化的农民的哀词。 2. This poem can be characterized as a lament for a dead lover. 这首诗可以看作是对死去情人的悼词。 3. The children lament the death of their mother. 孩子们哀悼母亲的去世。 4. She lament her son\'s death all night. 她整夜为儿子之死而悲伤。', '名词: lamenter 过去式: lamented 过去分词: lamented 现在分词: lamenting 第三人称单数: laments 形容词: lamenting 副词: lamentingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tranquil', '[\'træŋkwɪl]', 'adj.安静的；宁静的；稳定的；不变的', '1. The countryside is very tranquil, with less people. 乡下挺安静的，人没那么多。 2. Driven by primordial instinct, the salmon hurl themselves upstream to spawn in the same tranquil pools where they themselves were born. 由原始的本能所驱动，大马哈鱼会奋力逆流而上在它们出生的同一个安静的水池内产卵。 3. A peaceful and tranquil atmo here permeates the place. 这地方充满着一种宁静的气氛。 4. In this tranquil night, you may know what I am thinking? 在这个宁静的夜晚，你可知道我在想些什么吗？', '副词: tranquilly 名词: tranquilness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('measure', '[\'meʒər]', 'n.措施；量度；尺寸；程度；办法 v.测量；比较；给予；权衡', '1. The government has taken measures to restrain inflation. 政府已采取措施控制通货膨胀。 2. The standard kilogram is maintained as a measure of mass. 标准的千克是测量质量的量度 3. I want the suit made to his own measure. 我想要这套西装照他自己的尺寸做。 4. You are right in some measure. 从某种程度上来说你是对的。 5. They measured the height of the ceiling. 他们测量了天花板的高度。', '名词: measurer 过去式: measured 过去分词: measured 现在分词: measuring 第三人称单数: measures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barn', '[bɑːrn]', 'n.谷仓；牲口棚；车库；大而空荡的农屋', '1. The barn will store five tons of grain. 这个谷仓能放五吨粮食。 2. We took shelter from the storm in a barn. 我们在一个谷仓里躲避暴风雨。 3. The cows were feeding on hay in the barn. 母牛正在牲口棚里吃乾草呢。 4. Another barn has been built there. 另一个牲口棚建在那儿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laborious', '[lə\'bɔːriəs]', 'adj.艰苦的；费劲的', '1. Her work is a laborious task. 她的工作很艰苦。 2. Cleaning the forest is a laborious business. 清理树林是份艰苦的差事。 3. He has a laborious style of writing. 他的文笔不流畅。 4. Checking all the names was a slow, laborious job. 核对全部名字是件既慢又费劲的事。', '副词: laboriously 名词: laboriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('charge', '[tʃɑːrdʒ]', 'n.责任；电荷；指控；费用；照顾 vi.要价；充电；向前冲，冲锋；记在账上 vt.控诉；赊帐；给…充电；委以重任；归罪于；装填（炸药等）', '1. As group leader, you should take charge. 你身为组长, 应当负起责任来。 2. He was arrested on a charge of armed robbery. 他被指控犯武装抢劫罪而遭逮捕。 3. Rub the leather and the rubber will produce the charge. 摩擦皮毛和橡胶会产生电荷。 4. He was arrested on a charge of armed robbery. 他被指控犯武装抢劫罪而遭逮捕。 5. How much do you charge per unit? 你们每件要价多少呢？ 6. The suspect was charged with murdering his wife. 嫌疑犯被控诉为谋杀他的妻子。', '过去式: charged 过去分词: charged 现在分词: charging 第三人称单数: charges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('regimen', '[\'redʒɪmən]', 'n.养生法；生活规则；训练课程', '1. Under such a regimen you\'ll certainly live long. 你这样养生一定可以长寿。 2. Regimen books say that people should eat more seasonal vegetables and avoid unseasonal food. 养生书籍上讲，人应该多吃时菜，少吃反季节食品。 3. The doctor enforced a strict dietary regimen. 医生强制一套严格的饮食起居制度。 4. Missionaries must live simply, rise early and follow an arduous regimen of prayer, study and accosting strangers. 传教士生活必须很简单，早上起的很早并勤于祈祷，刻苦学习并和陌生人搭讪。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grieve', '[ɡriːv]', 'vt.使伤心；使悲伤 vi.悲伤；伤心', '1. It grieves me to see him in such bad health. 看见他的健康状况如此不佳，我很伤心。 2. It grieves me to hear how disobedient you\'ve been. 听说你很不听话，使我感到非常难过。 3. She was grieving for the dead baby. 她为死去的孩子悲伤。 4. It\'s no use grieving about past errors. 为过去的错误懊悔不已是无济于事的。', '副词: grievingly 名词: griever 过去式: grieved 过去分词: grieved 现在分词: grieving 第三人称单数: grieves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inhabit', '[ɪn\'hæbɪt]', 'v.居住于；占据；栖息', '1. Broadly, we investigate the world\'s lakes and rivers and the creatures which inhabit them. 宽广地，我们调查世界的湖和河和居住于他们的人。 2. Wookiees inhabit the upper levels of the forest, having built their massive cities within the interwoven canopy. 伍基人占据了树林的上层，并在交织的树冠上建造了巨大的城市。 3. Under Forman\'s tutelage, actors fully inhabit their roles, the hospital becomes an evil institution, and the movie poignantly celebrates the human spirit. 根据福尔曼的指导，演员完全占据自己的角色，医院成为一个邪恶的机构，和电影尖锐地庆祝人类的精神。 4. Many types of seabirds inhabit the coral island. 这个珊瑚岛上栖息着很多种海鸟。', '形容词: inhabitable 名词: inhabitability 过去式: inhabited 过去分词: inhabited 现在分词: inhabiting 第三人称单数: inhabits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spawn', '[spɔːn]', 'n.卵；产物；后代；结果 vt.产卵；种菌丝于；产生；造成 vi.产卵；大量生产', '1. I found a mass of spawn in the fish before cooking. 烧鱼前，我发现鱼里有很多鱼籽。 2. But bellicose intercontinental ballistic missiles were not the only spawn of Sputnik\'s launch.There was also the satellite itself. 洲际弹道导弹不是太空竞赛的唯一产物，卫星也是。 3. As a result, the mature female mud crab can spawn, though the number of eggs laid is affected. 结果表明精英的人工移植不会破坏成熟雌蟹纳精囊的内环境，其内精子具正常受精能力。 4. Many sea fishes spawn in rivers. 许多海洋鱼类是在淡水河里产卵的。 5. Probably this spawn was not fertilized. 这大概是产卵不受精。', '名词: spawner 过去式: spawned 过去分词: spawned 现在分词: spawning 第三人称单数: spawns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('witness', '[\'wɪtnəs]', 'n.目击者；证人 vt.目击；经历；见证；出席；观察 vi.证明；为(宗教信仰)做见证', '1. The witness was telling about the whole accident. 目击者正在讲述整个事故的过程。 2. The lawyer examined the witness. 律师讯问了证人。 3. A material witness failed to appear in court. 一名重要的证人没有出庭。 4. Did anyone witness the traffic accident? 有谁目击了这场交通事故？ 5. The empty cupboard was a witness of his poverty. 空的食橱就是他贫穷的证明。', '名词: witnesser 过去式: witnessed 过去分词: witnessed 现在分词: witnessing 第三人称单数: witnesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('peerless', '[\'pɪrləs]', 'adj.无比的；出类的；无双的', '1. Chinese silk is peerless in the world simply Because long practice has led to the way of perfection. 中国丝绸之所以天下夺魁，是因为长久的实践创造了完美。 2. To be a peerless man is very difficult. 做一个出类拔萃的人是很不容易的。 3. His Chinese kung fu is peerless. 他的中国功夫是无敌的。 4. Welcome to HongKong, a peerless city in entire world. 欢迎莅临香港，一个举世无双的城市。', '副词: peerlessly 名词: peerlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('given', '[\'ɡɪvn]', 'adj.特定的；假设的；有 ... 倾向的 prep.考虑到；如果 n.不争的事实 动词give的过去分词形式', '1. You have to finish the work within the given time. 你们必须在规定时间内完成这项工作。 2. The given radius being 4 ft., find the circumference. 已知半径为四英尺,求周长。 3. He is given to boasting. 他喜欢吹牛。 4. Given his age, he did it quite well. 考虑到他的年龄，他做得相当好。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decorum', '[dɪ\'kɔːrəm]', 'n.礼貌合宜', '1. Can you cancel a date with decorum? 你能够有礼貌地取消约会吗? 2. I hope you will behave with decorum at the funeral. 我们希望你在葬礼上做到得体有礼。 3. Each had enough decorum to suspend further hostilities. 双方都还有足够的礼貌，总算暂时停止了进一步的敌对行为。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('layer', '[\'ler]', 'n.层 vi.分层 vt.将某物堆积成层', '1. This layer of rock contains a lot of flint. 这一岩层中有大量燧石。 2. There is a fine layer of dust on the desk. 桌子上有一层薄薄的尘土。 3. There are several layers of meaning. 有几层不同的含意。 4. The pollution had destroyed ozone layer and caused many changes in weather. 污染破坏了臭氧层，并引起了许多天气变化。 5. Mists layered thick about him. 层层雾霭笼罩着他。 6. Layer the potatoes and onions in a dish. 把土豆和洋葱分层放在盘子里。', '过去式: layered 过去分词: layered 现在分词: layering 第三人称单数: layers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clot', '[klɑːt]', 'n.凝块；一群；<非正式>笨蛋 v.凝结；阻塞', '1. Ruby,convicted murdered of Oswald,died on January 3,1967 from a blood clot that lodged in his lungs. Ruby，曾经被指控谋杀Oswald，由于血液凝块进入肺部，死于1967年1月3日。 2. The pipe under the bathroom sink was jammed by a huge clot of hair. 浴室洗手台下的水管被一大团头发堵塞了。 3. A haemophiliac\'s blood will not clot properly. 血友病患者的血液凝固不良。 4. Researchers say the water dilutes the blood, making it less likely to clot. 研究人员说，水可以稀释血液，使之不易发生凝结。', '过去式: clotted 过去分词: clotted 现在分词: clotting 第三人称单数: clots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suspend', '[sə\'spend]', 'v.暂停；悬浮；中止；勒令停职', '1. As the workers went on strike, the company was obliged to suspend its operations. 由于工人罢工,该公司被迫暂停营运。 2. Such fine particles suspend readily in water. 这种微粒极易悬浮在水中。 3. They decided to suspend trade with that country. 他们决定中断和那个国家的贸易。 4. The policeman was suspended while the complaint was investigated. 因该警察遭投诉，在调查期间已令其暂停职务。', '过去式: suspended 过去分词: suspended 现在分词: suspending 第三人称单数: suspends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skull', '[skʌl]', 'n.头骨；骷髅头', '1. Have scientists found Mozart\'s skull? 科学家们已经找到了莫扎特的头骨吗? 2. Her skull had been fractured by two separate blows. 她的头骨在两次重击下骨折。 3. They stamped a skull and crossbones on the label of poisonous drug. 他们在毒药标签上打上骷髅图。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pledge', '[pledʒ]', 'vt.发誓；保证；以 ... 抵押；向 ... 祝酒 n.保证；抵押；誓言；抵押品', '1. They pledged never to tell the secret. 他们发誓决不泄密。 2. We all had to pledge allegiance to the flag. 我们大家都得发誓忠于这面旗帜。 3. She pledged her support to us. 她保证支持我们。 4. I pledge myself to fulfil the promise I have made. 我保证实践自己的诺言。 5. And as we walk, we must make the pledge that we shall march ahead. 当我们行动时,我们必须保证勇往直前。', '过去式: pledged 过去分词: pledged 现在分词: pledging 第三人称单数: pledges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conventional', '[kən\'venʃənl]', 'adj.传统的；惯例的；常规的', '1. Her book is a hilarious send-up of a conventional spy story. 她写的书用的是取笑传统侦探小说的笔法，令人捧腹。 2. According to conventional wisdom, voters usually make their choice on the basis of domestic issues. 按一般人在这些问题上的看法，选民常常着眼于国内问题来选择候选人。 3. After a conventional opening remarks, he made a brilliant speech. 在一个常规的开场白后,他做了个很精彩的演讲。 4. I can never get a girl like that with conventional methods. 我用寻常套路可永远也得不到这样的女孩。', '副词: conventionally 名词: conventionalism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('variable', '[\'veriəbl]', 'adj.可变的；易变的 n.变量；易变的东西', '1. Prices are variable according to the rate of exchange. 物价会随汇率而变动。 2. His mood is as variable as the weather. 他的情绪如天气般反覆无常。 3. The quality of the hotel food is distinctly variable. 这个旅馆的饭菜有时很好有时很差. 4. The temperature is a variable in the experiment. 在该实验中温度是个变量。', '副词: variably 名词: variableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ledge', '[ledʒ]', 'n.架状突出物；壁架；暗礁；岩脊', '1. He keeps some books on the window ledge. 他把一些书放在窗台上。 2. He eased himself along the ledge to reach the terrified boy. 他小心翼翼地沿着突出的檐向那惊惶失措的男孩靠近。 3. The ledge overhangs by several feet. 壁架凌空伸出几英尺。 4. Above the chimney were sundry villainous old guns, and a couple of horse-pistols: and, by way of ornament, three gaudily-painted canisters disposed along its ledge. 烟囱上挂着各式各样的锈了的老式枪，以及一对马上用的大型短枪。为了起到装饰作用，三个涂得很俗气得罐子，陈列在壁架上。', '形容词: ledgy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contemptible', '[kən\'temptəbl]', 'adj.可鄙的；可轻视的', '1. His cowardice in face of the enemy was contemptible. 他在敌人面前胆小如鼠，真是可鄙。 2. It\'s a contemptible trick to play on a friend! 这种手段欺骗朋友，真是卑劣！ 3. The bold man glanced at the gangster with hatred and contempt. 那个大胆的男人用嫌恶轻视的眼神目瞄了那个帮派份子一眼。', '副词: contemptibly 名词: contemptibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('implement', '[\'ɪmplɪmənt]', 'n.工具；器具；当工具的物品 vt.实施；执行；向 ... 提供工具(或手段)', '1. What implements are needed for gardening? 园艺需要些什么工具？ 2. That implement is useful for many purposes in the kitchen. 那种工具在厨房里有许多用途。 3. The system can preferably implement automatic text categorization for Chinese pages, and has a higher quality. 该系统可以很好地实现一个中文网页的自动分类，且系统中的分类器具有较高的分类质量。 4. Her designs will be put on ice until money is available to implement them. 她的设计将暂时搁起来，等有了钱再去实施。', '名词: implementation 过去式: implemented 过去分词: implemented 现在分词: implementing 第三人称单数: implements');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tedious', '[\'tiːdiəs]', 'adj.单调乏味的；沉闷的', '1. The tedious job simply ate me up. 那单调乏味的工作简直把我烦死了。 2. He told me a tedious story. 他给我讲了一个冗长乏味的故事。 3. He is an exceedingly tedious fellow. 他是一个非常令人生厌的家伙。 4. How can he give us such a tedious lecture. 他怎么能做这么沉闷乏味的演讲。', '副词: tediously 名词: tediousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allege', '[ə\'ledʒ]', 'vt.断言；宣称', '1. The newspapers allege that the police shot the suspect without warning. 报纸指称说警察未经示警就枪杀那位嫌疑犯。 2. So they alleged, but have they any proof? 他们是这样宣称的，但他们有证据吗？ 3. The police alleged that the man was murdered but they have given no proof. 警方声称这男子是被谋杀的，但未提出任何证据。 4. In your statement you allege that the accused man was seen at the scene of the crime . 在你的口供中，你供述曾经看到被告在犯罪现场。', '形容词: allegeable 名词: alleger 过去式: alleged 过去分词: alleged 现在分词: alleging 第三人称单数: alleges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thrive', '[θraɪv]', 'vi.兴旺；繁荣；茁壮成长', '1. A business cannot thrive without good management. 没有良好的经营管理，事业就不会兴旺发达。 2. But will they survive and thrive? 但是，他们会生存下来并兴旺繁殖吗? 3. May our country prosper and thrive forever! 希望我们的国家繁荣兴旺，长盛不衰。 4. A business can not thrive without investment. 没有投资任何生意都无法繁荣。', '名词: thriver 过去式: thrived/throve 过去分词: thrived/thriven 现在分词: thriving 第三人称单数: thrives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attachment', '[ə\'tætʃmənt]', 'n.附件；附属物；忠诚；依恋；附著；依赖 n.[法律]扣押令', '1. The attachment is combined with the contract. 1本合同附件是本合同不可分割的组成部分。 2. Please do not send your resume by attachment. 请勿以附件形式发送简历。 3. It\'s an electric drill with a range of different attachments. 这是一个带有各种配件的电钻。 4. She\'s on attachment to the Ministry of Defense. 她现在隶属于国防部。 5. The attachment of the offical has been reported by the national TV station. 这个官员被捕的消息已经被国家电视台报道了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('parade', '[pə\'reɪd]', 'n.游行；检阅；游行地 vi.参加游行；阅兵；散步；炫耀 vt.夸耀；使参加游行；检阅；绕行', '1. People wore historical costumes for the parade. 人们穿著古装参加游行。 2. The children flew out to see the parade. 孩子们奔出去看游行队伍。 3. No words can express the grandeur of that parade. 阅兵式那宏伟的场面是无法用语言表达的。 4. The general inspected the parade. 将军检阅了阅兵式。 5. The strikers paraded through the city center. 罢工队伍游行穿过市中心。 6. He is always parading his knowledge. 他总是夸耀自己的知识。', '名词: parader 过去式: paraded 过去分词: paraded 现在分词: parading 第三人称单数: parades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tenuous', '[\'tenjuəs]', 'adj.脆弱的；稀薄的；贫乏的；纤细的；空洞的', '1. Our existence is far more tenuous than we might think. 但我们的生命远比想像的要脆弱。 2. Cassini had passed through a tenuous cloud. 卡西尼号还曾经穿越过稀薄的云层。 3. The air ten miles above the earth is very tenuous. 地面往上十英里处的气体是非常稀薄的。 4. He gave a tenuous account of his past life. 他对他过去的生活说得很含糊。', '副词: tenuously 名词: tenuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('savor', '[\'seɪvə]', 'n. 味道； 气味； 滋味 vi. 有 ... 的味道或风味 vt. 调味； 品尝； 欣赏 =savour（英）', '1. Love life, only to survive in order to savor the taste of life, and feel the warmth of life, and create a brilliant life! 珍爱生命，只有生存下去，才能体味生命的滋味，感受生命的温暖，创造生命的辉煌！ 2. He needs to savor his victory. 他需要享受胜利的滋味。 3. So the next time you savor a new candy or potato chip, thank the flavorists. 所以下回你品尝新口味的糖果或土豆片时，要特别感谢这些调味学家。 4. I will savor its taste and give thanks. 一口一口，细细品尝，满怀感激。', '形容词: savorous 名词: savorer 过去式: savored 过去分词: savored 现在分词: savoring 第三人称单数: savors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disarm', '[dɪs\'ɑːrm]', 'v.放下武器；裁军；解除武装；缓和', '1. It is difficult to persuade them to disarm. 要说服他们放下武器是很难的。 2. The superpowers are unlikely to disarm completely. 超级大国不太可能彻底裁军。 3. The police disarmed the criminal. 警察缴下了罪犯的枪械。 4. The world has waited 12 years for Iraq to disarm. 全世界等待伊拉克解除武装已有12年之久。', '名词: disarmer 过去式: disarmed 过去分词: disarmed 现在分词: disarming 第三人称单数: disarms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pure', '[pjʊr]', 'adj.纯的；纯洁的；纯粹的', '1. Water can be made pure by distilling it. 水可以通过蒸馏而提纯。 2. They are all made of one-hundred percent pure silk. 它们都是用100%的纯丝绸做成的。 3. Life is a sweet thing for one who has a pure conscience. 对于善良纯洁的人来说,生活是一件美好的事情。 4. The look from her eye is still so pure, like a dustless crystal. 她的眼神依旧清纯,仿佛水晶般纤尘不染。', '副词: purely 比较级: purer 最高级: purest 名词: pureness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('means', '[miːnz]', 'n.方法；手段；收入；财产 v.意思是，意味（动词mean的第三人称单数）', '1. Are there any means of getting there? 有什么方法可以到那里吗？ 2. We express our thought by means of words. 我们用词句来表达思想。 3. He explored ways and means of solving the question. 他寻找解决问题的方法。 4. If other means fail we shall resort to force. 如果其他手段均告失败，我们将诉之武力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abridge', '[ə\'brɪdʒ]', 'v.删节；缩短；限制', '1. He decide to abridge his stay here after he receive a letter from home. 他接到家信后决定缩短在这里的逗留时间。 2. This is an abridged edition of \"war and peace\". 这是“战争与和平”的节略版。 3. It was abridged from the original work. 这是原书的节录本。', '名词: abridger 过去式: abridged 过去分词: abridged 现在分词: abridging 第三人称单数: abridges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contingent', '[kən\'tɪndʒənt]', 'n.代表团；小分队；偶然的事情 adj.取决于；经验主义的；不可预知的', '1. The largest contingent was from the United States. 最大的会议代表团来自美国。 2. A large contingent from Japan was present at the conference. 来自日本的一个大代表团出席了会议。 3. A contingent of 400 Thebans remained. 一支400名的提佛人的小分队也留了下来。 4. The naval contingent was expected to come. 我们期望海军分遣队到来。 5. Our arrival time is contingent on the weather. 我们的抵达时间取决于天气情况。', '副词: contingently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('escape', '[ɪ\'skeɪp]', 'v.逃跑；逃脱；逃避；被忘掉；泄露；去度假 n.逃跑；逃脱；逃避；泄露；度假；[计算机]退出键', '1. The prisoner has escaped. 犯人逃走了。 2. To my surprise, he could escape from that big fire. 令我惊讶的是,他能够从那场大火里逃脱出来。 3. I had left England to escape from my own future. 我离开英国是为了逃避自己的命运。 4. They came to America to escape political tyranny. 他们为逃避暴政逃到了美洲。 5. The thief jumped into a car and made his escape. 小偷跳上汽车逃走了。', '形容词: escapable 名词: escaper 过去式: escaped 过去分词: escaped 现在分词: escaping 第三人称单数: escapes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gratify', '[\'ɡrætɪfaɪ]', 'v.使满足；使高兴', '1. Now that she has a job in France she can gratify her desire to see Europe. 既然现在她在法国工作，那就可以满足她游览欧洲的愿望了。 2. I was gratified to see how much my birthday present was appreciated. 看到我的生日礼物受到极大的赞赏，我感到高兴。', '形容词: gratifying 副词: gratifyingly 名词: gratifier 过去式: gratified 过去分词: gratified 现在分词: gratifying 第三人称单数: gratifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glue', '[ɡluː]', 'n.胶；胶水；胶粘物 vt.粘贴；紧附于', '1. This extra strong glue should do the job nicely. 这种超强度胶应该管用。 2. This glue doesn\'t stick very well. 这种胶水粘不住。 3. The poster wouldn\'t stick even though I drenched it with glue. 我涂了大量胶水，可那张海报就是贴不住。 4. He glued a stamp onto the envelope. 他把邮票贴在信封上。', '形容词: gluey 名词: gluiness 过去式: glued 过去分词: glued 现在分词: gluing 第三人称单数: glues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entail', '[ɪn\'teɪl]', 'vt.使必需；带来；限定继承 n.限定继承权', '1. This job entails a lot of hard work. 这项工作需要十分努力。 2. It will entail driving a long distance every day. 这意味着每天都要长途开车。 3. The alteration would entail an expenditure of 50 pounds. 此项改变将带来为数五十英磅的花费。 4. He would have sold the property long ago had it not been entailed. 这些财产若非限定继承的话，他早就卖掉了。 5. You allude perhaps to the entail of this estate. 你大概是说产业的继承权问题。', '名词: entailment 过去式: entailed 过去分词: entailed 现在分词: entailing 第三人称单数: entails');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disfigure', '[dɪs\'fɪɡjər]', 'v.使丑陋；损毁(外貌等)', '1. The accident disfigured him for life. 那次事故使他毁容，终生无法恢复。 2. This landscape is disfigured by a power station. 风景被发电厂破坏了。', '名词: disfiguration 过去式: disfigured 过去分词: disfigured 现在分词: disfiguring 第三人称单数: disfigures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irrelevant', '[ɪ\'reləvənt]', 'adj.不恰当的；无关系的；不相干的', '1. Never pad out your essay with irrelevant details. 千万别用不相干的细节来拉长文章。 2. His death is irrelevant to the hospital. 他的死与医院没有关系。 3. This irrelevant paragraph may well be left out. 这一段与主题关系不大，满可以省略。 4. Our discussions got bogged down in irrelevant detail. 我们的讨论纠缠在无关紧要的细节上。', '副词: irrelevantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('staff', '[stæf]', 'n.员工；全体人员；全体职员；拐杖；杆；棒；五线谱 vt.配备员工', '1. I find the hotel staff particularly courteous. 我发现饭店员工特别谦恭有礼。', '名词复数: staffs 过去式: staffed 过去分词: staffed 现在分词: staffing 第三人称单数: staffs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fascinate', '[\'fæsɪneɪt]', 'vt.使 ... 入迷；吸引住 vi.有吸引力', '1. Anything to do with old myths and legends fascinates me. 任何与上古神话传说有关的东西都会使我着迷。 2. The place continues to fascinate visitors, cloaked in its mystery. 这个地方笼罩在神秘气氛下，继续使游览者着迷。 3. The students were fascinated by his ideas. 学生们都被他的思想吸引住了。 4. I watched her, fascianted. 我瞧着她,完全被她吸引住了。 5. It seems that the private lives of movie stars never fail to fascinate. 电影明星的私生活似乎总是使人津津乐道。', '过去式: fascinated 过去分词: fascinated 现在分词: fascinating 第三人称单数: fascinates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transitory', '[\'trænsətɔːri]', 'adj.暂时的；瞬息的；短暂的；片刻的', '1. Hunger may be long-term, or it may be transitory. 饥饿可能是长期的，也可能是暂时的。 2. These feelings tend to be transitory. 这些感觉多是暂时的。 3. We do not even have a transitory glimmer of hope. 我们连昙花一现的希望都没有。 4. Love is transitory but it is eternal. 爱情短暂却永恒。', '副词: transitorily 名词: transitoriness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('substantive', '[səb\'stæntɪv]', 'adj.独立的；真实的；持久的；本质的；名词性的；大量的；规定义务与责任的；实质的 n.作名词用的词或词组', '1. The airwaves are noisy with nonsense at a time when we need serious, substantive information. 当我们需要严肃而真实的信息的时候，电视广播却是充斥着废话的噪声。 2. The paper uses substantive cases to make it demotic and pellucid. 本文通过运用大量的案例分析，希望能使行文表达通俗易懂。 3. Its importance was evident from the large number of substantive proposals tabled during the ongoing discussion. 目前正进行的讨论中出现了大量的实质性提案体现了其重要意义。 4. It was a lengthy speech but he made few substantive points. 那是一个冗长的演说但是他整理很少实质的要点。', '副词: substantively 名词: substantiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bold', '[boʊld]', 'adj.大胆的；陡峭的；醒目的；粗体的；无礼的', '1. Bold outlines and warm colors characterize his dominate style in painting. 他大胆的绘画和所有的暖色调表现了他独有的绘画特色。 2. She was a shy girl, but she put on a bold front and went to the party. 她是个害羞的女孩子,然而她却装出一副勇敢的样子去参加聚会。 3. The peaks stood out in bold relief against the azure sky. 在蓝天的映衬下,山峰的轮廓极为明显。 4. A bold black headline screamed out from the front page. 在头版上出现了一条令人触目惊心的粗黑体大字标题。', '副词: boldly 比较级: bolder 最高级: boldest 名词: boldness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('errand', '[\'erənd]', 'n.差使；差事；跑腿', '1. It was not an errand that much pleased the doctor. 这种差使医生可不大喜欢干。 2. I have to go an errand for him now. 我现在得去听他的差遣。 3. I\'ve got a few errands to do in the town. 我有几件事要进城办。 4. You must do the two errands this week. 你必须在一周内完成这两项任务。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conscious', '[\'kɑːnʃəs]', 'adj.神志清醒的；意识到的；自觉的；有意的 n.意识', '1. His rudeness was conscious, not accidental. 他的粗暴无礼是故意的,不是偶然的。 2. He was conscious of his guilt. 他自知有罪。 3. I am conscious that I have done right. 我相信自己做得不错。 4. I had to make a conscious effort not to be rude to him. 我得刻意约束自己不要对他粗鲁。 5. ou avoid conflict between your conscious and subconscious in the sleepy state. 在你处于昏昏欲睡状态时，你要避免你的表意识和潜意识之间的冲突。', '副词: consciously');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mold', '[moʊld]', 'n.模式；类型；模子；模型；真菌；软土 vt.形成；制模；发霉 vi.发霉；符合形状', '1. Pictures help you to form the mental mold. 想象有助于你形成思想模式。 2. Chiefly the mold of a man\'s fortune is in his own hands. 一个人的命运模式主要是由自己决定的。 3. We need more people of his mold. 我们需要更多他那种类型的人。 4. And then you put them in a mold. 然后把它们放到一个模子里。 5. West culture has been molded by the Bible. 西方文化的形成受到《圣经》的巨大影响。 6. The cheese molded in the damp cellar. 乳酪在潮湿的地下室中长了霉。', '形容词: moldable 名词: molder 过去式: molded 过去分词: molded 现在分词: molding 第三人称单数: molds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extinct', '[ɪk\'stɪŋkt]', 'adj.灭绝的；熄灭的；消亡的', '1. This is an extinct species of fish. 这是一种已经灭绝的鱼。 2. This species will be extinct in a few decades. 几十年后这个物种将会灭绝。 3. An extinct volcano can no longer erupt. 一个灭绝的火山已不能再爆发。 4. My hope of getting some employment was extinct. 我要找到工作的希望落空了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('erratic', '[ɪ\'rætɪk]', 'adj.古怪的；飘忽不定的；不稳定的', '1. He was like a stormy, erratic boy. 他好象是个性急的古怪的孩子。 2. Though occasionally chatty, his moods were erratic. 他虽然有时健谈，但是他的脾气却很难捉摸。 3. An erratic mind jump from one idea to another. 心意不定的人反复无常。 4. They no longer fear the erratic behavior of the market. 他们永远不害怕市场飘忽不定的行为。', '副词: erratically 名词: erraticism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('erect', '[ɪ\'rekt]', 'vt.使竖立；建立；建造 adj.直立的；竖立的；笔直的', '1. They erected their tent at the foot of the mountain. 他们在山脚下支起了帐篷。 2. The town will erect a monument to its war heroes . 这个市镇将为该城的战斗英雄们立个纪念碑。 3. Six policemen started to erect a roadblock. 六个警察着手建立一道路障。 4. They plan to erect an apartment house on that property. 他们计划在那片地产上建造一座公寓楼。 5. She held her head erect and her back straight. 她昂着头，把背挺得笔直。', '形容词: erectable 副词: erectly 名词: erectness 过去式: erected 过去分词: erected 现在分词: erecting 第三人称单数: erects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embrace', '[ɪm\'breɪs]', 'v.拥抱；包含；包围；接受；信奉 n.拥抱', '1. We embraced each other. 我们互相拥抱。 2. She held out her arms to embrace the little girl. 她伸出双臂来拥抱那个小女孩。 3. Many subjects are embraced in an encyclopedia. 百科全书中包含许多科目。 4. We allowed the warm water to embrace us. 我们让温水包围我们 5. He enfolded the child in an affectionate embrace. 他疼爱得把孩子紧紧搂在怀里。', '形容词: embraceable 名词: embracement 过去式: embraced 过去分词: embraced 现在分词: embracing 第三人称单数: embraces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('animated', '[\'ænɪmeɪtɪd]', 'adj.生气勃勃的；栩栩如生的；动画片的', '1. Amongst the objects in the scene, they soon discovered an animated one. 她们很快在这些景物中发现了一个生气勃勃的目标。 2. Your colorful teeth and tongue may be calling attention to the vivid and colorful stories you tell and the animated way you express yourself. 你的鲜艳的牙齿和舌头可能是提醒大家注意你说的栩栩如生的故事以及你生动的表达自我的方式。 3. At Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, architectural students move around in an animated image of the Parthenon, examining that noble structure\'s roof and columns. 在伦塞勒工业学院，建筑专业的学生们围着一个栩栩如生的巴台农神庙图像转圈子，仔细研究那宏伟建筑的屋顶和圆柱。 4. The art or process of preparing animated cartoons. 摄制动画片的制作艺术或过程。', '副词: animatedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entrepreneur', '[ˌɑːntrəprə\'nɜːr]', 'n.企业家；承包商；主办者', '1. He is a shipping entrepreneur. 他是个航运企业家。 2. The entrepreneur has become a news figure. 这位企业家变成了新闻人物。', '形容词: entrepreneurial 名词: entrepreneurialism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squeak', '[skwiːk]', 'n.吱吱声；逃脱 v.吱吱叫；侥幸通过；<俚>告密', '1. With a rusty squeak, a pair of steel doors slid open. 伴随这因生锈而发出的吱吱声，两扇钢门打开了。 2. Shirley gave a little squeak of surprise. 雪莉轻轻地惊叫了一声。 3. The bill passed by a narrow squeak. 议案勉强通过了。 4. We\'ve pulled you through a tight squeak. 我们侥幸地助你通过了难关。 5. Can you hear the mice squeaking? 你听到老鼠吱吱叫吗?', '过去式: squeaked 过去分词: squeaked 现在分词: squeaking 第三人称单数: squeaks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('marked', '[mɑːrkt]', 'adj.有记号的；显著的；受监视的 v.弄污；打分；留意；做标记（动词mark的过去式和过去分词）', '1. They set a trap for him by putting marked money in to the till. 他们把有记号的钱放在钱屉里，设圈套抓他。 2. The voltage values at the marked locations should be measured and recorded. 应当把有记号处的电压值测量并记录下来。 3. They have made marked achievements in all fields. 他们在各个领域都取得了显著的成绩。 4. The output of cars shows a marked increase over last year. 汽车的产量比较去年有显著的增长。', '副词: markedly 名词: markedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('itinerant', '[aɪ\'tɪnərənt]', 'adj.巡回的；流动的 n.巡回者', '1. In the same year an itinerant black preacher arrived in Los Angeles. 就在同一年，一个黑人巡回传教士抵达了洛杉矶。 2. RIM has been stunningly successful, but even it has only around 3 million users, mostly itinerant corporate executives. 然而即使其仅有300万用户，且其中大多为飞来飞去的企业经理，RIM 已经是极其成功了。 3. Itinerant bike repairmen can be found on almost every street. 流动的自行车修理摊几乎在每条街道都可以找到。 4. There is a general debate nowadays about the problem of itinerant workers. 目前，针对流动工人的问题展开了普遍的争论。 5. Going on a trip or changing the apartment, Tiefschlaf is a must for any itinerant. 旅行中或者改变你的公寓,德国睡梦是巡游者的必需品。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hinder', '[\'hɪndər]', 'v.阻碍；打扰 adj.后面的', '1. The crowd hindered him from leaving. 人群使他无法脱身。 2. Heavy snow hindered the construction work. 大雪妨碍了这项建筑工程的进行。 3. Don\'t let me hinder you from going. 别让我妨碍了你走。 4. Don\'t hinder me. 不要妨碍我。 5. The hinder leg of this horse was broken. 这匹马的后腿断了。', '名词: hinderer 过去式: hindered 过去分词: hindered 现在分词: hindering 第三人称单数: hinders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reliable', '[rɪ\'laɪəbl]', 'adj.可靠的；可信的', '1. I don\'t think he is a reliable man. 我认为他不是一个可靠的人。 2. She may be slow but at least she\'s reliable. 她迟钝是迟钝，但无论如何她很可靠。 3. A reliable car is worth its weight in gold. 靠得住的汽车就是无价之宝。 4. A man who is dead to the justice is not reliable. 一个没有正义感的人是不可信的。', '副词: reliably 名词: reliability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('homage', '[\'hɑːmɪdʒ]', 'n.敬意；效忠', '1. Everyone pays homage to the soldiers. 每个人都对军人表示敬意。 2. But they freely concede that they will be there at the end as an act of homage. 但他们不得不勉强的承认他们会满怀敬意的守到最后时刻。 3. The Imperial Guards presented homage to the king. 皇家警卫队向国王宣誓效忠。 4. Investiture is distinct from homage. 授封和效忠不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ardent', '[\'ɑːrdnt]', 'adj.热心的；激烈的；热情的', '1. Some industrialists are at heart ardent reformers. 有些企业家实际上都是热心的改革家。 2. The satisfaction derived from this act was all that the most ardent moralist could have desired. 这个行动使自己得到了连最热心的慈善家都希冀得到的满足。 3. An ardent outset may be followed by declension. 热情的开端可能继之以冷漠。 4. I\'ve never met such an ardent pacifist as Terry. 我从未见过像特里这样热情的和平主义者。', '副词: ardently 名词: ardency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('musician', '[mju\'zɪʃn]', 'n.音乐家', '1. That musician is very famous. 那位音乐家非常有名。 2. He\'s not in the first grade as a musician. 他不是第一流的音乐家。 3. The musician made the legend into a beautiful ballad. 这位音乐家把传说编成了一首美丽的民谣。 4. She is a talented musician as well as being a photographer. 她不但是摄影师还是个天才的音乐家。', '形容词: musicianly 名词: musicianship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('infant', '[\'ɪnfənt]', 'n.婴儿；幼儿 adj.婴儿的；初期的；幼稚的', '1. She gazed at the newborn infant and smiled. 她望着这个初生的婴儿笑了。 2. My sister\'s infant is very lovely. 我姐姐的小婴儿非常可爱。 3. A 35-day-old male infant was scheduled for bilateral inguinal herniorrhaphy. 摘要一个三十五天大的幼儿接受二沟腹股沟疝气门诊手术。 4. Infant family education is an important education environment which can\'t be irreplaceable by preschool education and social education. 幼儿家庭教育是幼儿园教育和社会教育所不能替代的重要教育环境。 5. Infant mortality is still very high in some developing countries. 某些发展中国家的婴儿死亡率仍然很高。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('atom', '[\'ætəm]', 'n.原子；微粒', '1. Scientists have unlocked the secret of the atom. 科学家已经揭开了原子的秘密。 2. A molecule of water consists of two atoms of hydrogen and one atom of oxygen. 水分子含有两个氢原子和一个氧原子。 3. The atom bomb is the offspring of the 20th century physics. 原子弹是20世纪物理学的产物。 4. That cannot get up an atom of sympathy for them. 那并不能激发起人们对他们的丝毫同情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('natural', '[\'nætʃrəl]', 'adj.自然的；天然的；私生的', '1. It is natural that he should fall in love with such a beautiful girl. 他爱上那位美丽的姑娘是很自然的事。 2. I prefer to see animals living in their natural state. 我宁愿看处于野生状态的动物。 3. Leave her alone. She\'s natural crier. 别理她,她是个天生爱哭的人。 4. Harriet Smith was the natural daughter of somebody. 哈里特·史密斯是一位不知姓名的人的非婚生女。', '名词: naturalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('algebra', '[\'ældʒɪbrə]', 'n.代数学', '1. The boy can\'t figure out the algebra problems. 这个男孩做不出这道代数题。 2. It\'s easy to learn algebra. 学习代数很容易。 3. We\'ve learned algebra in middle school. 我在中学就学过代数学。', '名词: algebraist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gravity', '[\'ɡrævəti]', 'n.重力；庄重；严重；严肃', '1. He discoursed impressively on Newton\'s theory of gravity. 他讲述了牛顿的引力定律，给人以深刻的印象。 2. The stone rolled down the hill by gravity. 石头在重力作用下向山下滚去。 3. The force of gravity pulls things towards the earth\'s centre. 地心吸力把物体吸向地心。 4. The lunar gravity is about one-sixth that on earth. 月亮的引力大约为地球的六分之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exude', '[ɪɡ\'zuːd]', 'v.流出；渗出', '1. The hot sun made him exude sweat. 烈日晒得他汗流浃背。 2. Some successful men exude self-confidence. 有些成功的人流露出自信。 3. She does not exude maternal warmth. 她没有散发出母性的温暖。 4. Sweat exudes through the pores. 汗从毛孔中渗出。', '过去式: exuded 过去分词: exuded 现在分词: exuding 第三人称单数: exudes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spaceship', '[\'speɪsʃɪp]', 'n.宇宙飞船', '1. The computer decelerated the spaceship. 计算机使宇宙飞船减速。 2. Spaceship make it possible to travel to the moon. 宇宙飞船使去月球旅行成为可能。', '异体字: spaceship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('canopy', '[\'kænəpi]', 'n.天篷；遮篷；苍穹', '1. There is a canopy over the entrance. 入口处有一顶天篷。 2. The enclosed canopy opens upward from the rear to allow for entry and exit. 打开封闭的天篷向上从后方允许入境和出境。 3. The trees formed a leafy canopy above their heads. 树木在他们头顶上空形成了一个枝叶茂盛的遮篷。', '名词复数: canopies 过去式: canopied 过去分词: canopied 现在分词: canopying 第三人称单数: canopies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diagram', '[\'daɪəɡræm]', 'n.图解；图表 vt.用图解法表示', '1. She gave me a diagram of railway network. 她给了我一张铁路网图解。 2. The diagram had been copied with great precision. 该图表的复印件很精确。 3. He pointed at the diagram to illustrate his point. 他指着图表来说明他的论点。 4. He will diagram the entire procedure so that you can understand it more clearly. 他将把整个程序制成图表，这样你就会理解清楚了。', '形容词: diagrammable 副词: diagrammatically 过去式: diagrammed/diagramed 过去分词: diagrammed/diagramed 现在分词: diagramming/diagraming 第三人称单数: diagrams/diagrams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contract', '[\'kɑːntrækt]', 'n.合同；婚约；合约；契约 v.缩小；订合同；缩短；感染（疾病）；招致', '1. They had set a term to the contract. 他们已给合同定了期限。 2. Families sought favourable alliances, either by marriage or contract. 各个家庭通过婚姻或者婚约来建立有力的亲缘关系。 3. Several companies will bid for the contract. 数家公司要投标争取合约。 4. He managed to disengage himself from the contract. 他成功地为自己解除了契约义务。 5. The heat contracted the woollen garment. 高温让羊毛衣缩小了。', '形容词: contractible 名词: contractibility 过去式: contracted 过去分词: contracted 现在分词: contracting 第三人称单数: contracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scruple', '[\'skruːpl]', 'n.顾忌；迟疑 v.顾虑', '1. He has absolutely no scruples; he\'ll do anything to get what he wants. 他没有一点点顾忌，为了得到自己想要的东西，他什么事都做得出来。 2. She will tell lies without scruple. 她会肆无忌惮地说谎。 3. Jane did it at once, and made no scruple about it. 简毫不犹豫，立刻就办了。 4. Don\'t scruple to ask for anything you want. 你要什么请尽量讲。', '过去式: scrupled 过去分词: scrupled 现在分词: scrupling 第三人称单数: scruples');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('construct', '[kən\'strʌkt]', 'vt.建造；构筑；造(句) n.构想', '1. This factory was constructed by our company. 这家工厂是由我们公司建设的。 2. They are planning to construct a new supermarket. 他们正在计划建造一个新的超级市场。 3. You must learn how to construct a logical argument. 你必须学会怎样确立合乎逻辑的论点。 4. He taught us how to construct sentences. 他教我们怎样造句。 5. There is a contrast between lived reality and the construct held in the mind. 现实生活与头脑所持概念之间有明显差别。', '形容词: constructible 名词: constructor 过去式: constructed 过去分词: constructed 现在分词: constructing 第三人称单数: constructs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strip', '[strɪp]', 'v.剥去；剥夺；脱衣；除去 n.脱衣舞；长条；条状', '1. Elephants strip the leaves from trees. 大象剥去了树上的叶子。 2. It was wrong of him to strip his daughter of the right to education. 他不该剥夺他女儿受教育的权利。 3. Having been stripped of all his titles, he disappeared from public life. 他被剥夺一切荣誉之后，就从公共生活中消声匿迹了。 4. The children stripped off their clothes and jumped into the river. 孩子们脱掉衣服跳进河里。 5. You met me at a strip club. 你和我是在脱衣舞俱乐部里认识的。', '过去式: stripped 过去分词: stripped 现在分词: stripping 第三人称单数: strips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ravish', '[\'rævɪʃ]', 'v.强奸；使 ... 狂喜；抢夺', '1. I was ravished by her beauty. 我被她的美貌迷住了。', '名词: ravisher 过去式: ravished 过去分词: ravished 现在分词: ravishing 第三人称单数: ravishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imply', '[ɪm\'plaɪ]', 'vt.暗示；意指；含有 ... 的意义', '1. I don\'t wish to imply that you are wrong. 我无意暗示你错了。 2. What do you want to imply? 你要暗示什么? 3. His silence implied agreement. 他沉默不语意味着同意了。 4. Cheerfulness doesn\'t always imply happiness. 快活并不总是意味着幸福。', '过去式: implied 过去分词: implied 现在分词: implying 第三人称单数: implies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enlist', '[ɪn\'lɪst]', 'vt.征募；使入伍；获得...支持 vi.入伍；参与', '1. We must enlist more men. 我们必须征募更多士兵。 2. We enlisted them to serve as ushers at the meeting. 我们征集他们当会议招待员。 3. She tried to enlist our support in the cause of the charity. 她试图招揽我们在那慈善事业上的支持。 4. He enlisted when he was 18. 他18岁时入伍。', '名词: enlistment 过去式: enlisted 过去分词: enlisted 现在分词: enlisting 第三人称单数: enlists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stylized', '[\'staɪlaɪzd]', 'adj.程式化的；风格化的 动词stylize的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Much of this work seeks to comprehend, in stylized theoretical settings, the unfolding of economic events over time. 这其中，大量的工作尝试着在一种程式化的理论背景下，去了解经济事态随着时间变化的演变。 2. For the interior Volvo has continued the sporty theme by adding aluminum inserts in the steering wheel, door mouldings and the stylized center stack. 为室内沃尔沃继续运动主题加上铝插入方向盘，门装饰和程式化的中控台。 3. The showdown with Mr.Fu is a stylized slow-mo sequence with men on both sides holding umbrellas with the surreal air of a Magritte painting. 付先生的摊牌是一个风格化的慢动作，两个人拿着伞彼此张望着，就像充满了超现实主义的氛围的玛格丽特油画。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('illicit', '[ɪ\'lɪsɪt]', 'adj.非法的；违禁的；不正当的', '1. The police chief was talking about the illicit sale of drugs. 警长在讲毒品的非法贩卖。 2. Illicit trades should be outlawed. 非法交易应被取缔。 3. He makes a lot of money by traffic illicit merchandise. 他做违禁商品买卖赚了许多钱。 4. He had an illicit association with Jane. 他和简曾有过不正当关系。', '副词: illicitly 名词: illicitness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consort', '[\'kɑːnsɔːrt]', 'n.<正式>（君王的）配偶；一组(古乐器)；一组(演奏几世纪前音乐的乐师) v.厮混；结交', '1. The queen consort has come together with the king. 王后也随同国王前来。 2. Don\'t consort with criminals. 不要和犯罪分子结交。 3. If Mary and Kate were friends, then to consort with Kate was one way of keeping in touch with Mary. 如果玛丽和凯特是朋友，那么与凯特交往就是与玛丽保持联系的一个途径。', '过去式: consorted 过去分词: consorted 现在分词: consorting 第三人称单数: consorts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('economize', '[ɪ\'kɑːnəmaɪz]', 'v.节约；节省；有效地利用 =economise（英）', '1. This new machine will help economize on raw materials. 这台新机器将有助于节约原材料。 2. Our electricity bills are higher than we can afford–we must start to economize. 我们的电费已经高得付不起了——得节省些了。', '名词: economizer 过去式: economized 过去分词: economized 现在分词: economizing 第三人称单数: economizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idiocy', '[\'ɪdiəsi]', 'n.愚蠢；白痴行为', '1. Such behavior is the ultimate in idiocy. 这样的行为愚蠢透顶。 2. It\'s sheer idiocy to go climbing in such bad weather. 在这样恶劣的天气里去爬山简直是愚蠢到家了。 3. His talking about it on the other hand is just pure idiocy. 他后来说的那些话只能算是白痴的呓语。', '名词复数: idiocies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stun', '[stʌn]', 'vt.使震惊；使目瞪口呆；使昏迷 n.震惊；晕眩', '1. This speech seemed to stun the king. 这话似乎使国王大吃一惊。 2. He was stunned by the sudden news. 他因听到这突然的消息而目瞪口呆。 3. She sat stunned for a while, until she recovered. 她一时昏迷，坐下呆了一会儿才醒过来。 4. The punch stunned me for a moment. 那一拳把我打得昏了一阵。 5. How do I set a laser printer to stun? 我怎么把一台激光打印机设置到震惊？', '过去式: stunned 过去分词: stunned 现在分词: stunning 第三人称单数: stuns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ablaze', '[ə\'bleɪz]', 'adj.着火的；闪耀的；激昂的', '1. The whole building was soon ablaze. 整座建筑物很快就烧起来了。 2. By the time firefighters were called the house was well ablaze. 消防队员接到火警电话时，房子已是一片火海。 3. The palace was ablaze with lights. 那座宫殿灯火辉煌。 4. The streets are ablaze with decorations. 街道装饰得五彩缤纷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('provident', '[\'prɑːvɪdənt]', 'adj.有先见之明的；节俭的', '1. Some of the farmers had been provident in the good years but others were ruined by the bad harvests. 有些农民在丰年节衣缩食有备无患，但也有些农民由於歉收而陷入绝境。 2. Provident men lay aside money for their families. 深谋远虑的人为家庭贮蓄钱财。 3. She has been provident since she was young, so she is thrifty in shopping. 她从小节省惯了，买东西的时候很节俭。', '副词: providently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plaintiff', '[\'pleɪntɪf]', 'n.原告', '1. The plaintiff accused the defendant of fraud. 原告指控被告欺诈。 2. Plaintiff is an antonym of defendant. 原告是被告的反义字。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('propel', '[prə\'pel]', 'v.推进；驱使', '1. He used a paddle to propel the boat. 他用船桨将船推进。 2. The proper use of imagination can then propel ideas in the directions you desire. 适当运用想象力可以将思想往你所希望的方向推进。', '过去式: propelled 过去分词: propelled 现在分词: propelling 第三人称单数: propels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('estimate', '[\'estɪmət]', 'n.估价；估计 v.估计；估价；评价', '1. This is an outside estimate of the price. 这是最高的估价。 2. Your estimate was rejected by the seller. 你的估价单被卖家回绝了。 3. This is a safe estimate. 这是个有把握的估计。 4. We need to make an accurate estimate beforehand. 我们需要事先作出准确的估计。 5. I estimate it will take three months to build the bridge . 我估计建造这座桥得用3个月时间。', '形容词: estimative 名词: estimator 过去式: estimated 过去分词: estimated 现在分词: estimating 第三人称单数: estimates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('progress', '[\'prɑːɡres]', 'n.进步；发展；前进 v.进步；发展；缓速前进；促进', '1. The student is showing rapid progress in his studies. 这个学生学习上进步很快。 2. Physics has made enormous progress in this century. 本世纪物理学的发展突飞猛进。 3. They made slow progress towards the mountaintop. 他们向山顶缓慢地前进。 4. He continues to progress in his studies. 他的学业继续取得进步。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('submission', '[səb\'mɪʃn]', 'n.提交；服从；屈服；[律]意见', '1. They prepared a report for submission to the council. 他们准备了一份报告要提交给理事会。 2. Tomorrow is the last date for submission of entries for the competition. 明天是提交参赛表格的最后期限。 3. They bowed to the king with all due submission. 他们必恭必敬地向国王鞠躬。 4. They believe that submission in no way implies inferiority. 他们认为服从决不意味着低人一等。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bounce', '[baʊns]', 'vi.弹起；重新恢复；退票 vt.使弹起；解雇；驱逐 n.弹跳；弹力；活力', '1. The ball hit the wall and bounced off it. 球打在墙上又反弹回来。 2. She\'s had many misfortunes in her life but she always bounces back. 她一生中经历过许多挫折，然而总是能重新振作起来。 3. He is young enough to bounce back from this disappointment. 他很年轻，能够从这次挫折中恢复过来。 4. I hope this cheque doesn\'t bounce. 我希望这张支票别遭退票 5. I bounced the baby on my knee. 我把婴儿放在膝上上下颠着。 6. The volleyball gave a high bounce. 排球高高地弹起来。', '过去式: bounced 过去分词: bounced 现在分词: bouncing 第三人称单数: bounces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bonus', '[\'boʊnəs]', 'n.红利；意外所得之物；奖金；【篮】追加罚篮', '1. The firm offered her a generous bonus as a sweetener. 公司提出给她一笔可观的花红借以拉拢她。 2. He received a box of cookies as a bonus when he bought coffee at the shop. 他在商店买咖啡时,意外地得到了一盒免费赠送的饼干。 3. The warm weather in such a freezing winter has been a real bonus. 这么寒冷的冬天有这样暖和的天气真是令人喜出望外。 4. The firm repaid her hard work with a bonus. 公司发给她奖金以酬谢她的辛勤工作。', '名词复数: bonuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('metabolic', '[ˌmetə\'bɒlɪk]', 'adj.新陈代谢的', '1. Especially during exercise, drink mineral water significantly improved fatigue, and speed up the metabolic rate, the rapid restoration of physical strength. 特别是运动时，饮用矿物质水能明显改善乏力状态，加快新陈代谢的速度，迅速恢复体力。', '副词: metabolically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('centigrade', '[\'sentɪɡreɪd]', 'adj.摄氏的；百分度的', '1. This thermometer is calibrated by centigrade. 这种温度计是用摄氏百分度标定的。 2. It is therefore usually expressed in percentage terms rather than in engineering units such as degrees centigrade. 因此它往往用一个百分比来表示而不是机械单位如百分度表示。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attach', '[ə\'tætʃ]', 'v.附上；系上；贴上；使依附；使附属；使附着', '1. I attach a copy of my notes for your information. 我附上笔记一份供你参考。 2. In confirmation hereof we attach a bank statement. 为作这方面的确认我们附上银行结单。 3. Please attach these labels to your hand luggages. 请把这些标签系在您的手提行李上。 4. Please attach your business card below or fill up the information. 推荐人请在下面框中贴上您的名片,如不贴名片,则请详细填写框中各项。', '形容词: attachable 名词: attachment 过去式: attached 过去分词: attached 现在分词: attaching 第三人称单数: attaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('courteous', '[\'kɜːrtiəs]', 'adj.有礼貌的；殷勤的；客气的，谦恭的', '1. It was courteous of him to help the old lady with her bundles. 他很有礼貌地帮助那个老太太扛包裹。 2. Bill is always a courteous youth. 比尔是个有礼貌的青年。 3. He was very courteous and well spoken. 他非常殷勤好客，说话又漂亮。', '副词: courteously 名词: courteousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stall', '[stɔːl]', 'n.栅栏；小隔间；货摊；座位 v.把...关进畜舍里；失速；熄火；拖延；（使）动弹不得', '1. The excited horse flung about in the stall. 受惊的马在马厩里乱冲乱踢。 2. The horse chafed against his stall. 马在厩栏上擦著身子。 3. Our house has a shower stall. 我们房子里有淋浴小隔间。 4. Never buy food from a market stall. 千万别在小摊上买食物。 5. You\'d better stall the pigs. 你最好把猪关在猪圈里饲养。', '过去式: stalled 过去分词: stalled 现在分词: stalling 第三人称单数: stalls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('professional', '[prə\'feʃənl]', 'adj.职业的；专业的；专门的 n.专业人员', '1. Don\'t wear those clothes to work; try to look more professional! 别穿这些衣服去工作，要穿得象个专业人员的样子。 2. That doctor has been accused of professional misconduct. 那位医生被指控违反医德。 3. She was always punctual and professional. 她总是准时并具有专业能力。 4. He is a professional journalist. 他是一位专门的新闻从业人员。 5. She is a real professional. 她是个真正的专家。', '副词: professionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hierarchy', '[\'haɪərɑːrki]', 'n.等级制度；统治集团；[生]级系', '1. There is a hierarchy in all living creatures. 一切生物均可按等级分类。 2. It\'s not as if he was very important in the company hierarchy. 他在公司的领导层中似乎无多大权力。 3. pull silver', '名词复数: hierarchies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('supersede', '[ˌsuːpər\'siːd]', 'vt.取代；接替；废弃', '1. Will factory workers be entirely superseded by machines one day? 工人将来能完全由机器取代吗? 2. Motorways have largely superseded ordinary roads for long-distance travel. 高速公路多已取代了普通公路。 3. The use of robots will someday supersede manual labor. 机器人的使用有一天会取代人力。 4. Any one could supersede you as manager in my office. 我办公室中的任何一个人都可以接替你的经理职务。', '名词: superseder 过去式: superseded 过去分词: superseded 现在分词: superseding 第三人称单数: supersedes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acquisitive', '[ə\'kwɪzətɪv]', 'adj.想获得的；贪得无厌的；可学得的', '1. It is an acquisitive company looking for ways to expand. 这是一家十分想要寻求扩张的公司。 2. He is acquisitive of money. 他十分贪财。 3. She has an acquisitive mind. 她有一颗好学之心。', '副词: acquisitively 名词: acquisitiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('checked', '[tʃekt]', 'adj.格子花纹的；棋盘花纹的 v.检查；阻止；核对（动词check的过去式和过去分词）', '1. She was carrying a straw basket covered with a blue checked cloth. 她挎着一个秸秆编成的篮子，篮子用一块蓝格子花纹布盖着。 2. Robert is wearing his checked suit. 罗伯特穿那套格子的衣服。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convenience', '[kən\'viːnjəns]', 'n.便利；舒适；适宜；便利设施；方便的时间', '1. It\'s a great convenience to live in town. 住在城市里有很大的方便。 2. I stock upon grocery at the convenience store. 我到便利商店买食品备用。 3. The hotel combines comfort with convenience. 这家旅馆既舒适又方便。 4. Analyzed experiment data, the best one is ultrasonic in the light of convenience, quick, especially avoid sample color disturbing and hydrargyrum pollution. 通过实验得出数据，进行分析，确定了超声法为最适宜样品前处理方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impressionism', '[ɪm\'preʃənɪzəm]', 'n.印象派；印象主义', '1. Manet is a painter of impressionism. 莫奈是印象派画家。 2. Impressionism changed the way people thought about art. 印象派改变了人们对于艺术的看法。 3. Many people classified my watercolor painting style as realistic impressionism. 许多人分类了我的水彩画样式作为现实印象主义。 4. She differed from early realists as much as cubism from impressionism. 她与早期那些现实主义作家不同，就象立体主义和印象主义不同一样。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subspecies', '[sʌb\'spiːʃɪz]', 'n.亚种', '1. Along a cline,subspecies with distinct characteristics may arise. 在变异群中，带有明显特征的亚群可能产生。', '形容词: subspecific 名词复数: subspecies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fashion', '[\'fæʃn]', 'n.时尚；风格；样子 vt.形成；塑造', '1. She was the queen of fashion during the 60s. 她是60年代的时尚女王。 2. Research shows that men are beginning to follow fashion. 研究显示,男性也开始像女性那样追求时尚。 3. She paints in the fashion of Picasso. 她模仿毕加索的绘画风格。 4. He only put a bit on his plate to make fashion. 他只是拨了一点食物到盘子里做做样子。 5. He managed to fashion a doll from a piece of wood. 他成功地用木块制成了一个玩具娃娃。', '名词: fashioner 过去式: fashioned 过去分词: fashioned 现在分词: fashioning 第三人称单数: fashions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sphere', '[sfɪr]', 'n.范围；领域；球；球体；天体 vt.形成球体；包围；围绕', '1. It belongs to the ideological sphere. 这属于意识形态范围。 2. The scientist is distinguished in many spheres of knowledge. 这位科学家在许多知识领域中都是杰出的。 3. Suddenly, out in the night sky, a bright sphere flashed into view. 突然，外面的夜空上有一个闪光的球映入眼帘。 4. The earth is an oblate sphere. 地球是一扁圆球体。', '名词: sphericity 过去式: sphered 过去分词: sphered 现在分词: sphering 第三人称单数: spheres');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jumble', '[\'dʒʌmbl]', 'vi.掺杂；混杂 vt.使混乱；搞乱 n.混杂；混乱 n.环形小甜饼', '1. This might be compared with the jumble of wavelengths of sound that go to make up ordinary noise. 这种现象可以与合在一起构成普通噪音的声波波长的混杂情况相比。 2. Reminiscent of experimental film or abstract expressionist paintings, the software creates an animated jumble of bright and energetic abstract light compositions. 实验电影或抽象表现主义绘画让人回想起该软件创建了一个明亮的光线和有力的抽象作品动画混杂。 3. This might be compared with the jumble of wavelengths of sound that go to make up ordinary noise. 这种现象可以与合在一起构成普通噪音的声波波长的混杂情况相比。 4. Reminiscent of experimental film or abstract expressionist paintings, the software creates an animated jumble of bright and energetic abstract light compositions. 实验电影或抽象表现主义绘画让人回想起该软件创建了一个明亮的光线和有力的抽象作品动画混杂。', '过去式: jumbled 过去分词: jumbled 现在分词: jumbling 第三人称单数: jumbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('threaten', '[\'θretn]', 'v.威胁；恐吓；似将发生', '1. The rebels threatened to seize civilian hostages. 叛乱分子威胁要扣押平民为人质。 2. The strikers were threatened with dismissal if they did not return to work. 罢工者受到威胁说，如果他们不复工，就会被解雇。 3. They threatened him with a law suit. 他们以控告来恐吓他。 4. The black clouds threatened rain. 乌云密布预示着将要下雨。', '副词: threateningly 名词: threatener 过去式: threatened 过去分词: threatened 现在分词: threatening 第三人称单数: threatens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amenable', '[ə\'miːnəbl]', 'adj.顺从的；通情达理的；经得起检验的；对...负有义务的', '1. They had three very amenable children. 他们有三个很听话的孩子。 2. We are amenable to the law . 我们应该服从法律。 3. He is proud that his wife is amenable to reason. 他的妻子是个通情达理的人,为此他引以为豪。 4. This case is not amenable to the normal rules. 这件事经不起常规的检验。', '副词: amenably 名词: amenability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legislation', '[ˌledʒɪs\'leɪʃn]', 'n.法律；法规；立法', '1. The new legislation is highly discriminatory. 新的法案，有许多地方厚此薄彼。 2. We protect the interests of investors by the legislation in effect. 我们根据现行法律保护投资者的利益。 3. The legislation was made retrospective. 该项法规具有追溯效力。 4. The government will introduce legislation to restrict the sale of firearms. 政府将制定法规限制枪支出售。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('novelty', '[\'nɑːvlti]', 'n.【C】新奇；小装饰 n.【U】新奇的事物；新奇的经验', '1. The novelty of his surroundings soon wore off. 他对环境的新奇感不久就淡薄了。 2. The demand is for quality, variety and novelty. 现在需求的是质量、花式品种和新颖性。 3. I bought some novelties on the boardwalk. 我在海滨人行道上买了一些新颖的小玩意儿。 4. Upon the whole the novelty attracted him. 总的说来，这个新奇的事物吸引着他。', '名词复数: novelties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sober', '[\'soʊbər]', 'adj.清醒的；稳重的；沉着冷静的；颜色暗淡的 vt.使清醒；使沉着 vi.清醒；冷静下来', '1. He was tipsy yesterday , but now is sober. 他昨天醉醺醺的,但现在是清醒的。 2. We should make a sober estimate of the situation. 我们对形势要有清醒的估计。 3. He is a very sober and hard-working young man. 他是一个非常稳重而勤奋的年轻人。 4. He talked with us in a sober and friendly fashion. 他以冷静而友好的方式同我们交谈。 5. He drank a cup of strong tea to sober himself up. 他喝下一杯浓茶以使自己清醒过来。 6. He sobered up quickly when he heard the terrible news. 他听到这个坏消息，马上就清醒过来了。', '副词: soberly 比较级: soberer 最高级: soberest 名词: soberness 过去式: sobered 过去分词: sobered 现在分词: sobering 第三人称单数: sobers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('torpid', '[\'tɔːrpɪd]', 'adj.迟钝的；无精打采的；冬眠的', '1. Marked by lethargy; torpid. 惰怠的以懒惰为特征的; 呆钝的', '副词: torpidly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arrange', '[ə\'reɪndʒ]', 'vt.整理；安排；计划；改编(乐曲) vi.协商；计划', '1. You must arrange these books in alphabetical order. 你要把这些书按字母顺序排好。 2. I have arranged one of my staff to meet you at the airport. 我已经安排好一个职员到飞机场接你。 3. If you can arrange the tourist destinations for me, I will be very grateful. 如果你能为我计划一下,我将不胜感激。 4. I have arranged with the neighbours about taking care of the cat. 我已和邻居们商量好照顾猫咪的事情。', '名词: arranger 过去式: arranged 过去分词: arranged 现在分词: arranging 第三人称单数: arranges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('despoil', '[dɪ\'spɔɪl]', 'v.夺取；掠夺', '1. A region despoiled of its scenic beauty by unchecked development. 由于不加限制的发展而使这个地区丧失了其美丽景色 2. Museums have despoiled India of many priceless treasures. 博物馆里有许多从印度掠夺来的无价之宝。', '名词: despoiler 过去式: despoiled 过去分词: despoiled 现在分词: despoiling 第三人称单数: despoils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('valiant', '[\'væliənt]', 'adj.勇敢的；英勇的 n.勇士；勇敢的人', '1. Let\'s hail to the valiant victors. 让我们向勇敢的胜利者致敬！ 2. A large reception was held in honor of the valiant explorers. 为勇敢的探险家们举行了一个盛大的招待会。 3. The valiant hero saved the little girl\'s life. 那个英勇的英雄拯救了小女孩的生命。 4. The man put up a valiant fight for victory. 这个人为了赢得胜利进行了英勇的斗争。 5. To a valiant heart nothing is impossible. 勇士面前无难事。', '副词: valiantly 名词: valiancy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chat', '[tʃæt]', 'vi.闲谈；谈天 n.闲谈；聊天', '1. He came round last week and we chatted for a while. 上星期他顺道来访,我们闲谈了一会。 2. He likes to chat with his e-pals on the Internet. 他喜欢上网与网友聊天。 3. Ask him to stop by for a chat. 请他来坐坐，聊聊天。 4. It is pleasant to chat with friends, and with no chat is it more pleasant than with close friends. 和朋友聊天是愉快的，而这种情形没有比和知己的朋友聊天更为愉快。', '过去式: chatted 过去分词: chatted 现在分词: chatting 第三人称单数: chats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enactment', '[ɪ\'næktmənt]', 'n.(法律的)制定颁布；法规', '1. Enactment into law of a legislative measure. (议案)通过把立法议案制定为法律 2. The enactment states that ... 法律规定 ...', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tamper', '[\'tæmpər]', 'v.干预；玩弄；贿赂；篡改', '1. By allowing the sacred mystery to unfold without trying to tamper with it, we can move through anything with much more ease and simplicity. 让恐惧的迷雾散开，不要去干预，这样的话，度过任何事情我们就能带着多的多的从容和简单。 2. It is dangerous for children to tamper with gunpowder. 孩子们玩弄火药是危险的。 3. You shouldn\'t tamper with a jury. 你不应该贿赂陪审团。', '名词: tamperer 过去式: tampered 过去分词: tampered 现在分词: tampering 第三人称单数: tampers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cavern', '[\'kævərn]', 'n.大洞穴 v.置于洞穴中；挖空', '1. The girl lost her way in the cavern. 女孩在大洞穴中迷了路。 2. They explored the large cavern at the base of this cliff. 他们勘探了这个悬崖底部的大洞穴。', '过去式: caverned 过去分词: caverned 现在分词: caverning 第三人称单数: caverns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('celestial', '[sə\'lestʃl]', 'adj.天上的；非凡的 n.天神 Celestial. adj.中国的；中国人的 n.中国人', '1. The rosy light yet beamed like a celestial dawn. 玫瑰色的红光依然象天上的朝霞一样绚丽。 2. She is a celestial bodhisattva and an ascended master. 她是天上的菩萨和已提升的大师。 3. And if living in the lower celestial and Brahma realms, their heads are always turned towards the higher planes of those worlds. 虽然他们还在低层的天神界以及梵天界，从那时起，就会转生较高级的天神界以及梵天界。', '副词: celestially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gallery', '[\'ɡæləri]', 'n.美术馆；画廊；顶层楼座；走廊', '1. The gallery has a show of French oil painting. 这个美术馆在展出法国油画。 2. She is a frequent visitor to the gallery. 她经常参观这个美术馆。 3. The gallery is a treasure trove of medieval art. 这个画廊是中世纪艺术的宝库。 4. There\'s a new picture show at the gallery tomorrow. 明天在画廊有个新画展。', '形容词: galleried 名词复数: galleries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rage', '[reɪdʒ]', 'n.狂怒；大怒；狂暴；肆虐；风行 v.大怒；怒斥；激烈进行；肆虐', '1. He was mad with rage. 他快要气疯了。 2. I was gnashing my teeth with rage. 我咬牙切齿愤怒已极。 3. He flew into a rage at the news. 他听到这个消息勃然大怒。 4. The storm showed elemental rage in its violence. 这场风暴显示了大自然的狂暴力量。 5. You are not yourself when you rage like that. 你那样大发雷霆有点失常。', '过去式: raged 过去分词: raged 现在分词: raging 第三人称单数: rages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advanced', '[əd\'vænst]', 'adj.先进的；高级的', '1. England is an advanced industrial country. 英国是一个发达的工业国家。 2. The ancient Egyptians had advanced civilization. 古埃及人曾经拥有高度文明。 3. Our bean curd processing line is the most advanced and well- know in the world. 我们的豆腐生产线是世界上最为先进的，久负盛名。 4. The regent carried out an advanced system in his country. 摄政者在他的国家推行了一套先进的制度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('modem', '[\'moʊdem]', 'n.调制解调器', '1. Does your computer have a modem? 你的电脑有调制解调器吗？ 2. Please select the modem you want to install. 请选择想要安装的调制解调器。 3. I can\'t hear if my modem is dialing. 我无法听到调制解调器是否在拨号。 4. Using a modem to connect to the internet is a thing of the past. 使用调制解调器上网已经过时了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cram', '[kræm]', 'v.塞满；猛吃；仓促备考 n.仓促备考；挤成一堆的人群 Cram. n.克拉姆(姓氏或男子名)', '1. This box is crammed with Christmas gifts. 这个盒子里塞满了圣诞礼物。 2. He crammed as much candy into his pockets as they would hold. 他把口袋都塞满了糖果。 3. I managed to cram down a few mouthfuls of food. 我好歹狼吞虎咽地吃了几口东西。 4. The teacher tried to cram his pupils. 老师试图用填鸭式教学把知识灌输给学生。 5. My son go to cram school every evening. 我的儿子每晚都去上补习班。 6. Cram ran a fine race to take the gold medal. 克拉姆在赛跑中成绩突出夺得金牌。', '名词: crammer 过去式: crammed 过去分词: crammed 现在分词: cramming 第三人称单数: crams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sociology', '[ˌsoʊsi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.社会学；<生>群落生态学', '1. Economics and sociology are social sciences. 经济学和社会学都属于社会科学。 2. A few years ago, sociology is the most popular subject for undergraduate. 几年之前，社会学是大学本科生最欢迎的课程。', '形容词: sociologic 副词: sociologically 名词: sociologist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acoustic', '[ə\'kuːstɪk]', 'adj.听觉的；声音的；原声的；音响的', '1. You must have an acoustic problem. 你的听觉一定有问题。 2. Acoustic beauty is also very important to the modern gardens. 园林听觉美对现代景观的效果也起到了很好的作用。 3. These have very good acoustic insulation which will help cut out external sounds. 这些具有非常好的隔音效果，能够帮助隔离外界的声音。 4. Once, I backpacked around Europe and I brought an acoustic guitar with me. 有一次，我轻装环游欧洲，随身带着一把原声吉他。', '副词: acoustically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heritage', '[\'herɪtɪdʒ]', 'n.遗产；继承物', '1. One of the glories of the British heritage is the right to a fair trial. 英国人引以自豪的传统之一是有获得公正审判的权利。 2. A novelist must be able to use the cultural heritage of his nation. 小说家要善于利用他本国的文化遗产。 3. These beautiful old palaces are part of our national heritage. 这些美丽的古老宫殿是我们民族遗产的一部分。 4. It is the heritage of all human beings. 这都是整个人类继承的东西', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gravitational', '[ˌɡrævɪ\'teɪʃənl]', 'adj.重力的；引力作用的', '1. It is a spontaneous gravitational instability. 原因在于其自发的重力不稳定性。 2. They are likely sources of gravitational waves. 它们很有可能就是引力波源。 3. Properties of space must depend on the gravitational potential. 空间性质一定与引力势有关。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glorify', '[\'ɡlɔːrɪfaɪ]', 'v.美化；赞美', '1. The setting sun glorified the scene. 落日使景色更美。 2. The newspapers glorified their heroic deeds. 报纸称颂了他们的英雄事迹。 3. Singing hymns is one of the ways to glorify god. 唱圣歌是赞美上帝的一种方式。', '名词: glorification 过去式: glorified 过去分词: glorified 现在分词: glorifying 第三人称单数: glorifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('particle', '[\'pɑːrtɪkl]', 'n.颗粒；微粒；极小量；质点；粒子；[语]小品词', '1. We can see the dust particles floating in the sunlight clearly. 我们可以很清楚地看到阳光下的灰尘颗粒。 2. An atom is the smallest indivisible particle of matter. 原子是最小的不可分的物质微粒。 3. There wasn\'t a particle of truth in what he said. 他说的没有一点真话。 4. The particle is displaced in a flow domain. 这质点在流动区域内运动。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('radius', '[\'reɪdiəs]', 'n.半径范围；半径；桡骨；辐射区', '1. Nobody is allowed to enter the operation radius. 不允许任何人进入工作半径范围以内。 2. What is the radius of this circle? 这个圆的半径有多长? 3. We can compute the circular area with radius. 我们能用半径计算出圆的面积。 4. The radius expands markedly at its lower end. 桡骨下端明显扩张。', '名词复数: radii');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fantasy', '[\'fæntəsi]', 'n.幻想 v.幻想', '1. The young always live in a world of fantasy. 年轻人总是生活在幻想中。 2. He is unable to divorce fantasy from reality. 他不能将幻想与现实分开。 3. He fantasies himself a doctor. 他想像自己是一位医生。', '名词复数: fantasies 过去式: fantasied 过去分词: fantasied 现在分词: fantasying 第三人称单数: fantasies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('placid', '[\'plæsɪd]', 'adj.平静的；宁静的；温和的', '1. For the next two months, life in the village went its placid way. 接下来的两个月，村中的生活一如既往的平静。 2. Her idea of love was more that of placid affection, serving the loved one softly in an atmosphere, flower-scented and dim-lighted, of ethereal calm. 她把爱情看得更像是平静的温情，在一个花香馥郁、光影迷离、虚无缥缈、万籁俱寂的氛围里，被拿来温柔地献给心爱的人。 3. I enjoy the placid pace of village life. 我喜欢宁静的乡村生活。 4. The heavens were placid, but still luminous with the light at the retreating sun. 天空一片宁静，夕阳染得天际色彩斑斓。', '副词: placidly 名词: placidity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hectic', '[\'hektɪk]', 'adj.忙乱的；兴奋的；[医]发热的；发红的', '1. I had a hectic day in the office. 我在办公室里忙乱了一天。 2. It can be a hectic life on a 24-hour news channel. 24小时新闻频道的生活可能非常忙乱。 3. The journalist leads a hectic life. 新闻记者过着紧张兴奋的生活。 4. Hectic phobophobia can be cured. 赤面恐怖症是可以治疗的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hardly', '[\'hɑːrdli]', 'adv.几乎不；简直不；刚刚', '1. Hardly anybody came. 几乎没有人来。 2. He could hardly refrain himself. 他几乎不能自制。 3. The desert air contains hardly any moisture. 沙漠的空气几乎不含一点湿气。 4. He is so excited that he can hardly sleep. 他如此兴奋，几乎不能入睡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stalk', '[stɔːk]', 'n.茎；梗 n.跟踪；高视阔步 v.悄悄靠近；跟踪；蔓延；高视阔步地走', '1. It doesn\' t produce a stalk at all the first year? 在头一年绝对长不出茎秆? 2. He cut off the flowers at the stalk with a pair of scissors. 他用剪子连花带茎都剪下来。 3. He ate the apple, stalk and all. 他把那个苹果吃了个干净，连梗都没剩下。 4. He moved like a tiger stalking its prey. 他像老虎一样悄悄潜近他的猎物。', '形容词: stalky 名词: stalker 过去式: stalked 过去分词: stalked 现在分词: stalking 第三人称单数: stalks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gratuitous', '[ɡrə\'tuːɪtəs]', 'adj.无缘无故的；无必要的；免费的', '1. I did not want to be singled out for gratuitous punishment. 我不愿意被叫出来遭受这无缘无故的惩罚。 2. His films are full of gratuitous violence. 他拍的影片充满了不必要的暴力。 3. His criticism is quite gratuitous. 他的批评完全没有根据。', '副词: gratuitously 名词: gratuitousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preserve', '[prɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'v.保护；保存；保持 n.禁猎区；蜜饯', '1. It is highly important to preserve the environment. 保护自然环境至关重要。 2. It\'s the duty of the police to preserve the public order. 维护公共秩序是警察的职责。 3. You should preserve your papers for future use. 你应当把你的文件保存起来以备将来之用。 4. I tried to preserve my independence. 我试图保持自己的独立性。 5. No hunting is allowed in the preserve . 在禁猎区内不许打猎。', '形容词: preservable 名词: preservability 过去式: preserved 过去分词: preserved 现在分词: preserving 第三人称单数: preserves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('afflicting', '[ə\'flɪktɪŋ]', 'adj.痛苦的 动词afflict的现在分词形式.', '1. She was afflicted with conscience. 她受良心责备。 2. Violent crime is only one of the maladies afflicting modern society. 暴力犯罪仅仅是危害社会的弊病之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('endless', '[\'endləs]', 'adj.无止境的；没完没了的', '1. Endless desires eventually led him astray. 无止境的欲望最终将他引入了歧途。 2. I can\'t endure your endless complaints anymore. 我再也不能忍受你无止境的抱怨了。 3. I am too busy to listen to her endless grievance. 我太忙了，没空听她那没完没了的牢骚。 4. We feel boring about his endless querimony. 我们对他没完没了的埋怨感到厌烦。', '副词: endlessly 名词: endlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vogue', '[voʊɡ]', 'n.时尚；流行', '1. Hoop skirts were once the vogue. 圈环裙一度曾是时尚。 2. Now Vogue has delivered the same for men\'s wear. 如今,时尚已同样进入男装。 3. Decorate become a war, a gamble, a vogue is performed. 装修成为一场战争，一场赌博，一场时尚表演。 4. Short hair came back into vogue. 短发又开始流行起来了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('soccer', '[\'sɑːkər]', 'n.足球，英式足球', '1. People love to play soccer. 人们喜欢踢足球。 2. The boy who is speaking to Helen enjoys playing soccer. 正在跟海伦谈话的那男孩喜爱踢足球。 3. The Government intends to clamp down on soccer hooliganism. 政府拟采取措施严禁在足球比赛中闹事。 4. In soccer, only the goal-keeper may play the ball with his hands. 在足球运动中只有守门员可以用手触球。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apparent', '[ə\'pærənt]', 'adj.明显的；表面上的', '1. It was apparent to all that he was guilty. 众所周知，他是有罪的。 2. Japan\'s apparent lack of capitalist endeavour also has much to do with the lack of a mature financing market. 显而易见,日本缺少资本家的创业精神,而这与日本没有一个成熟的融资市场也有很大关系。 3. She had many good qualities despite her apparent rudeness. 她粗鲁是粗鲁，但还有许多优秀品质。 4. If she had inner doubts, it was not apparent to anyone else. 她若心中生疑亦不形之于色。', '副词: apparently 名词: apparentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legendary', '[\'ledʒənderi]', 'adj.传说的；传奇的；著名的', '1. Do you believe that the legendary Loch Ness monster exists? 你相信传说的尼斯湖水怪存在吗? 2. He is a legendary hero. 他是个传奇式的英雄。 3. His legendary escape from prison would never be forgotten. 他传奇般的越狱永远不会被忘记。 4. Her patience and tact were legendary. 她的耐心和机智是出名的。', '副词: legendarily');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convoy', '[\'kɒnvɔɪ]', 'n.护航队；护送；护卫；警护 v.护航；护送', '1. Two fighters buzzed the convoy as it approached the coast. 当护航队接近海岸时,两架战斗机飞近示警。 2. In a few hours, the destroyer drew on the convoy. 几小时后，驱逐舰就赶上了护航舰队。 3. The supply ships sailed under convoy. 补给船在护送之下航行。 4. The missiles were moved under convoy. 导弹在护卫之下转移. 5. The troop ships were convoyed across the Atlantic. 运兵船被护送渡过大西洋。', '过去式: convoyed 过去分词: convoyed 现在分词: convoying 第三人称单数: convoys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ratio', '[\'reɪʃioʊ]', 'n.比率；比例', '1. The ratios of 1 to 5 and 20 to 100 are the same. 1与5之比和20与100之比相同。 2. Men outnumber women here in the ratio of three to one. 此地男子数量以三比一超过女子。 3. The ratio of schoolboys to schoolgirls is 2 to 1. 男学生和女学生的比例是2比1。 4. The ratio of nursing staff to doctors is 2:1. 护士和医生的比例是2：1.', '名词复数: ratios');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glossy', '[\'ɡlɑːsi]', 'adj.光滑的；有光泽的', '1. He tickled gently at its glossy carapace, but the stubborn beetle would not budge. 他轻轻地搔着甲虫光滑的壳，但这只固执的甲虫就是不动。 2. In order to give chewing gum balls a glossy surface, they are treated with Bees or Carnauba wax in appropriate implements. 为了使某些口香糖有一个光滑的外壳，通常制造商会用适当的设备处理蜂蜜或巴西棕榈蜡。 3. Tufted evergreen perennial herb having spikes of tiny white flowers and glossy green round to heart-shaped leaves that become coppery to maroon or purplish in fall. 多年生常绿簇生草本植物，有白色小花穗，圆形或心形有光泽的绿叶，秋天从古铜色变成褐紫红色或紫色。', '副词: glossily 比较级: glossier 最高级: glossiest 名词: glossiness 名词复数: glossies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('moth', '[mɔːθ]', 'n.蠹；蛾', '1. Its colour makes the moth indistinguishable from the branch it rests on. 这蛾子停在树枝上，其颜色和树枝几不可辨。 2. A moth was fluttering round the lamp. 有一只蛾子扑打著翅膀绕著灯飞。 3. The moth quivered its wings. 蛾子抖动著翅膀。 4. This piece of cloth was eaten by a moth. 这块布被蠹虫蛀坏了。', '名词复数: moths');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irony', '[\'aɪrəni]', 'n.反讽；讽剌之事', '1. The good point is that the irony fully reflected. 好的地方是反讽完全出来了。 2. Irony was widely used in the works of Kafka and LuXun. 卡夫卡和鲁迅的小说中都广泛应用了反讽的艺术手法。 3. The great irony is that despite all his explanation nobody believed him. 最具讽刺意味的是：尽管他竭力解释，可没一个人相信他。 4. After Peanuts left,I could not help thinking about this irony. 落花生去后，我总是不住的这样想这件讽刺的事。', '名词复数: ironies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flake', '[fleɪk]', 'n.薄片；小片；火花 v.剥落', '1. The natural form of carbon in cast iron is the free graphite flake form. 铸铁内的碳天然形式是游离石墨薄片形式。 2. Flakes of rust are falling from the old iron pan. 一片片的锈从旧铁锅上落下。 3. Meeting you is the flake of my life. 遇见你是生命中的火花。 4. The paint\'s beginning to flake off. 油漆开始成薄片状剥落。', '名词: flaker 过去式: flaked 过去分词: flaked 现在分词: flaking 第三人称单数: flakes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('declivity', '[dɪ\'klɪvətɪ]', 'n.倾斜面；斜坡', '1. Franz and the count in their turn then advanced along the same path, which, at the distance of a hundred paces, led them over a declivity to the bottom of a small valley. 弗兰兹和伯爵也顺着这条小径向前走去，走了约一百步，他们就到了一片通到一个小谷底去的斜坡上。', '名词复数: declivities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inhabitant', '[ɪn\'hæbɪtənt]', 'n.居民', '1. Every inhabitant here has an obligation to pay taxes. 这里的每一位居民都有纳税的义务。 2. The inhabitant can see the Church House and the Death House， but never the exterior of the Court House. 居民也能看到教会安置和死囚刑前的住房，但从未见过法院的外貌。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coral', '[\'kɔːrəl]', 'n.珊瑚 adj.珊瑚的；珊瑚色的', '1. Coral is formed by certain types of polyp. 珊瑚是由某些水螅体构成的。 2. There are lots of coral in the sea. 海里有许多珊瑚。 3. Although the coral is moveless , it is alive. 珊瑚虽然一动不动,但其实是活体。 4. The ship was wrecked on a coral reef. 那艘船触珊瑚礁失事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chalk', '[tʃɔːk]', 'n.粉笔；白垩 v.用粉笔写；记录；使变白；归咎', '1. The teacher wrote on the blackboard with a piece of chalk. 老师用一支粉笔在黑板上写字。 2. The teacher\'s chalk grated on the blackboard. 老师的粉笔在黑板上发出刺耳的摩擦声。 3. My father said cement couldn\'t be made from chalk. 我父亲说水泥不能用白垩来制作。 4. The boys chalked out goalposts on the playground wall. 男孩子们在运动场的墙上用粉笔画上了球门柱。', '形容词: chalky 名词: chalkiness 过去式: chalked 过去分词: chalked 现在分词: chalking 第三人称单数: chalks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incorporate', '[ɪn\'kɔːrpəreɪt]', 'v.合并；组成公司 adj.合并的；公司组织的', '1. I will incorporate the new findings in my report. 我要把新发现并入我的报告。 2. This company is about to incorporate with its parent company. 这公司将要与其母公司合并。 3. We had to incorporate for a company for tax reasons. 鉴于税务原因，我们得组成公司。', '形容词: incorporable 名词: incorporation 过去式: incorporated 过去分词: incorporated 现在分词: incorporating 第三人称单数: incorporates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pleasing', '[\'pliːzɪŋ]', 'adj.使人满意的；令人愉快的；讨人喜爱的 动词please的现在分词.', '1. We have made pleasing progress in our talks. 我们的会谈已经取得了令人满意的进展。 2. It was even more pleasing to look at in the morning light. 它在早晨的光线下看起来更悦目。 3. This painting has a pleasing balance of shapes and colours. 这幅画在构图和色彩方面都十分谐调。 4. The arrangement of the furniture formed a pleasing ensemble. 这些家具摆放得悦目而和谐。', '副词: pleasingly 名词: pleasingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fret', '[fret]', 'v.(使)烦恼；(使)焦急；(使)磨损；侵蚀 n.烦躁；磨损；焦急 n.[音]音品；音柱', '1. You always get yourself into a fret over nothing. 你总为了莫须有的事，把自己弄得烦恼不已。 2. Don\'t fret over these small details. 不要为这些小事烦恼。 3. But Canadians are grumpy.They worry about government ethics, but they fret even more about things like the state of their health-care system. 但是加拿大人是乖戾的，他们担心政府的道德问题，但他们更为诸如医疗保健体制状况之类的问题焦急。 4. As she spoke we could see that she was in a fret. 她讲话时，我们看得出她很烦躁。', '过去式: fretted 过去分词: fretted 现在分词: fretting 第三人称单数: frets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('utility', '[juː\'tɪləti]', 'n.效用；实用；公用事业（费）；[计]应用程序 adj.多效用的；多功能的', '1. I have always doubted the utility of these conferences on disarmament. 我一直怀疑这些裁军会议的效用。 2. Their research project has limited practical utility. 他们的研究项目实用价值很有限。 3. Does your rent include utilities? 房租包括水电和煤气的费用吗？ 4. Utility prices, including water, electricity, gas, rose by 5.6 per cent. 水、电、煤气在内的公用事业价格都上涨了5.6%。', '名词复数: utilities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idealize', '[aɪ\'diːəlaɪz]', 'v.(使)理想化；理想化地描述', '1. I warned you not to idealize me. 我告诫过你不要把我理想化。 2. This is probably true, and it may explain why some of us idealize such societies. 这可能是对的，它解释了为什么我们常会理想化这些社会。', '名词: idealization 过去式: idealized 过去分词: idealized 现在分词: idealizing 第三人称单数: idealizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excerpt', '[\'eksɜːrpt]', 'n.摘录 vt.摘录；引用', '1. This is an excerpt from a novel. 这是一部小说的摘录。 2. I\'ve seen a short excerpt from the film on television. 我在电视上看过这部影片的片段。 3. You can excerpt passages from a book. 你可以从一本书中摘录几段。 4. Can you excerpt something from the newspaper? 你能从报纸上选录些东西吗?', '过去式: excerpted 过去分词: excerpted 现在分词: excerpting 第三人称单数: excerpts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interval', '[\'ɪntərvl]', 'n.间隔；休息时间；(数学)区间；(音乐)音程', '1. He comes back to see us at regular intervals. 他每隔一段时间就回来看看我们。 2. The proper intervals should be maintained between vehicles. 车辆之间应保持适当的间距。 3. The performance runs 2 hours 30 minutes including an interval. 整个演出2小时30分,包括中间休息。 4. These equations are interval linear equations. 该控制方程是线性区间方程组。', '形容词: intervalic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grievance', '[\'ɡriːvəns]', 'n.委屈；冤情；苦况', '1. The idea makes me feel a sense of grievance. 我突然感到很委屈。 2. He will not easily forget his grievance. 他不会轻易忘掉他的委屈。 3. He used the occasion to express all his old grievance against the chairman. 他利用那机会表达了对主席积压已久的怨气。 4. A committee was set up to look into the workers\' grievances. 成立了一个委员会来调查工人的不满。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crack', '[kræk]', 'v.破裂；砸开；发出爆裂声；撞击；破解；变嘶哑；崩溃；制裁；<非正式>开玩笑 n.裂缝；裂痕；爆裂声；猛击；尝试；俏皮话 adj.训练有素的', '1. The glass will crack if you pour boiled water into it . 一倒进去滚开水，这个玻璃杯就会破裂。 2. You may crack these nuts with a hammer. 你可以用锤子把这些坚果敲开。 3. I cracked two eggs into the frying pan. 我往平底锅里打了两个鸡蛋。 4. Thunder cracked overhead. 雷在头顶上炸响了。 5. There is a crack in this window. 这扇窗户上有个裂纹。 6. She is a crack shot with a rifle. 她是步枪神枪手。', '过去式: cracked 过去分词: cracked 现在分词: cracking 第三人称单数: cracks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glorious', '[\'ɡlɔːriəs]', 'adj.光荣的；辉煌的；<口>愉快的', '1. She is always bucking about her glorious past. 她老是吹嘘她的光荣的过去。 2. It is a task at once glorious and arduous. 这样的任务是非常光荣的，但同时也是非常艰巨的。 3. The picture reminds me of my glorious past. 这幅画使我想起了我辉煌的过去。 4. Our country has a glorious past. 我们的国家有一段光辉的历史。', '副词: gloriously 名词: gloriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vital', '[\'vaɪtl]', 'adj.至关重要的；有活力的；生死攸关的', '1. The government saw the introduction of new technology as vital. 政府认为引进新技术至关重要。 2. She\'s a very vital sort of person. 她是个精力旺盛的人。 3. Confronted with such a vital problem of life and death, he looked as cool as a cucumber. 面对着这样重大的生死问题,他的神态却异常冷静。', '副词: vitally 名词: vitalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('covetous', '[\'kʌvətəs]', 'adj.贪婪的；贪心的；垂涎的', '1. She shows a covetous look. 她露出贪婪的表情。 2. He was never covetous before he met her. 在遇到她之前，他从不贪婪妄羡。 3. You are so covetous, eating the food in the bowl and looking at the pot. 你真贪心 4. He is covetous of her high salary. 他垂涎她的高薪。', '副词: covetously 名词: covetousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('human', '[\'hjuːmən]', 'adj.人的；人类的；有人性的；人本性的 n.人；人类', '1. The accident was caused by human error. 这宗事故是人为过失造成的。 2. It is beyond the confines of human knowledge. 这超出了人类的知识范围。 3. Her novel shows her keen insight into human character. 她的小说显示出她对人性的敏锐洞察力。 4. His cruelty suggests that he is less than human. 他的残忍表示他没有人性。 5. He was the only human on the island. 他是那个岛上唯一的人。', '名词: humanhood');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bankruptcy', '[\'bæŋkrʌptsi]', 'n.破产；倒闭', '1. The bank of bankruptcy is investigated by the court. 那家破产的银行正被法院调查。 2. Ten bankruptcies were recorded in this town last year. 去年这个镇已有十起破产事件。 3. The prospect of bankruptcy has now receded. 破产的危险已经减少了。 4. The government has rescued the firm from bankruptcy by giving them a grant. 政府拨款给这家公司使其免于破产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cultivation', '[ˌkʌltɪ\'veɪʃn]', 'n.教化；培养；耕作', '1. Pity is acquired and improved by the cultivation of reason. 怜悯是靠理性的教化而获得和发展起来的。 2. Only rigid cultivation can enable a man to find truth in a lie. 只有头脑僵硬的教化，才能使一个人从一个谎言中找到事实。 3. Read for the cultivation of a sound quality. 培养高尚的品质。 4. It only needs early cultivation to become a power. 只需及早培养，记忆自会成为一种才能。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dusky', '[\'dʌski]', 'adj.微黑的；带黑的；昏暗的', '1. Gold earrings gleamed against her dusky cheeks. 金色的耳环在她微黑的面颊上闪闪发光。 2. His dusky skin is a sign of healthiness. 他黑黝黝的皮肤是健康的标志。 3. The whole theatre roared in the dusky light. 在昏暗的灯光下，整个剧院里一片喧嚣。', '副词: duskily 比较级: duskier 最高级: duskiest 名词: duskiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('automatic', '[ˌɔːtə\'mætɪk]', 'adj.自动的；无意识的；必然的 n.自动装置；半自动武器', '1. This heating system has an automatic temperature control. 这个暖气系统有自动化的温度调节系统。 2. We get an automatic increase in pay every year. 我们的薪金每年会自动增长。 3. For most of us breathing is automatic. 我们大多数人的呼吸都是无意识的。 4. A fine for this offence is automatic. 对于这种过失,罚款是必然的。 5. We now consider it to be the primordial automatic device because it held the first breath of lifelikeness in a machine. 而我们现在之所以把它看成是自动装置的鼻祖，是因为它在一个机器装置中成功地把握到了生命之为生命的第一次呼吸。', '副词: automatically 名词: automaticity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rod', '[rɑːd]', 'n.杆；棍棒；竿', '1. The concrete walls are reinforced with steel rods. 混凝土墙是用钢筋加固的。 2. He sank the metal rod in before the concrete set. 他在混凝土凝固之前把金属棒插了进去。 3. I knew I was in trouble when I was taken to the garage with a rod. 当我被人拿著棍棒赶到车库时,我知道我惹下麻烦了。 4. I bought a new fishing rod last Sunday. 上星期日我新买了一个鱼竿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tragic', '[\'trædʒɪk]', 'adj.悲剧的；悲惨的', '1. This delay was to have tragic results. 这样的延误即将导致悲剧的结局。 2. I don\'t like the tragic ending of the film. 我不喜欢电影悲剧的结尾。 3. Her tragic story touched us all deeply/touched our hearts with sorrow. 她的经历很悲惨，我们都深受感动[我们都很伤心]。 4. She listened to the tragic news ashen-faced. 她听到这一悲惨消息，脸都白了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prey', '[preɪ]', 'n.牺牲者；被掠食者，猎物 vi.掠夺；捕食；使 ... 苦恼', '1. She fell (a) prey to melancholy. 她为忧郁所折磨。 2. She was easy prey for dishonest salesmen. 她很容易地让奸商敲了竹杠。 3. The lion seized its prey and ate it. 狮子抓住猎物，把它吃了。 4. The eagle seized its prey in a tenacious grip. 鹰将捕获物紧紧抓住。 5. In those far- off times Viking pirates used to prey on the coasts of Europe. 在那些遥远的时代里，北欧海盗经常在欧洲海岸一带进行掠夺。', '名词: preyer 过去式: preyed 过去分词: preyed 现在分词: preying 第三人称单数: preys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slumber', '[\'slʌmbər]', 'n.睡眠；微睡；休止状态 v.睡觉；打盹；静止；休眠', '1. Don\'t wake him from his slumber because he needs the rest. 不要把他从睡眠中唤醒，因为他需要休息。 2. Three girls are still slumbering peacefully. 3个女孩仍在平静地睡着。', '副词: slumberingly 名词: slumberer 过去式: slumbered 过去分词: slumbered 现在分词: slumbering 第三人称单数: slumbers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('caribou', '[\'kærɪbuː]', 'n.北美驯鹿', '1. They used caribou skins for tents. 他们用驯鹿的皮做帐篷。 2. We also wear handmade boots, which are made from caribou skin or sealskin. 我们穿的靴子也是手工制作的，是用北美驯鹿的皮或海豹皮制成的。', '名词复数: caribou');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impropriety', '[ˌɪmprə\'praɪəti]', 'n.不适当；不正确；用词错误；不得体', '1. He waved off suggestions of impropriety. 他撤消了不适当的建议。 2. The investigation revealed no impropriety. 调查表明没有不正当的做法. 3. They were shocked by the impropriety of the young man\'s action. 他们为那年轻人的不当举止而感到震惊。 4. Impropriety is the soul of wit. 用词不当是打趣话的精髓。', '名词复数: improprieties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lawn', '[lɔːn]', 'n.草坪；草地', '1. My mother asked me to mow the lawn. 妈妈让我去剪草坪。 2. Let\'s have tea on the lawn. 我们到草坪上去喝茶吧。 3. Moles dug tunnels under the lawn. 鼹鼠在草地下面打洞。 4. The reception was held in a pavilion on the lawn. 招待会在草地中的亭子里举行。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abrasion', '[ə\'breɪʒn]', 'n.擦伤；磨损；磨损处', '1. She was treated for cuts and abrasions. 她的割伤和擦伤得到了治疗。 2. Diamonds have extreme resistance to abrasion. 钻石极抗磨损。 3. The rivet heads on the bucket are in good condition and without severe abrasion. 扣件铆钉钉头状况良好，并无严重磨损。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inherent', '[ɪn\'hɪrənt]', 'adj.固有的；内在的', '1. Weight is an inherent property of matter. 重量是物质固有的特性。 2. The desire for freedom is inherent in us all. 渴望自由是我们大家生来就有的愿望。 3. She has an inherent love of beauty. 她天生爱美。 4. There is an inherent weakness in the design. 这设计本身存在弱点。', '副词: inherently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scent', '[sent]', 'n.气味；香味；线索 v.闻出；发觉；充满；得到 ... 的暗示', '1. The dog easily picked up the scent of the murderer. 狗毫不费力地嗅出了谋杀者的气味。 2. The scent was of leaves and turned earth. 这是树叶和新翻泥土的气味。 3. Through the window I caught the scent of syringa. 从窗口我闻到紫丁香的香味。 4. His nostrils dilated with the scent of the air. 他的鼻孔因为空气中的香味而张大了。 5. The dog scented a rat. 那狗嗅出有老鼠的气味。', '形容词: scentless 过去式: scented 过去分词: scented 现在分词: scenting 第三人称单数: scents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stark', '[stɑːrk]', 'adj.严酷的；荒凉的；光秃秃的；鲜明的 adv.完全；实在；简直', '1. He now faces the stark reality of life in prison. 他现在要面对狱中生活的严酷现实了。 2. Those afflicted with the stark problem of how to keep on living. 受维持生计的严酷问题困扰的那些人们。 3. The landscape was grey and stark. 景色灰暗荒凉。 4. The tree has only stark branches. 这棵树只剩下光秃秃的树枝。 5. The fool is talking stark nonsense. 这傻瓜完全是在胡扯。', '副词: starkly 比较级: starker 最高级: starkest 名词: starkness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('juncture', '[\'dʒʌŋktʃər]', 'n.时刻；关头；接合；连接；[语]连音', '1. At the most critical juncture we took turns in watching that point. 在最为紧急的时刻，我们轮流监视着那个地方。 2. At this juncture his office door opened. 正在这个关头，他的办公室的门开了。 3. The project is situated at the juncture of the new and old urban districts. 该项目位于新老城区交界处。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('personality', '[ˌpɜːrsə\'næləti]', 'n.个性；名人；特色', '1. His personality comes through in his writing. 他的个性体现在他的文章中。 2. She has a very strong personality. 她个性很强。 3. He is one of the best-known personalities in the world of tennis. 他是网球界最著名的人物之一。 4. His wife was very beautiful, but seemed to have no personality. 他的妻子很漂亮,但似乎没有什么特点。', '名词复数: personalities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oasis', '[oʊ\'eɪsɪs]', 'n.绿洲；宜人之地', '1. This desert of unattractiveness has its oasis . 在这一片枯燥无味的沙漠上，也有一座绿洲。 2. They stopped for the night at an oasis. 他们在沙漠中的绿洲停下来过夜。 3. Borne on the back of the ship of the desert, we reached the oasis at sunset. 我们骑着骆驼，在太阳落山时到达了这块绿洲。 4. The study is an oasis of calm in a noisy household. 在喧闹的家中，书房可谓宁静之一隅。', '名词复数: oases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('airborne', '[\'erbɔːrn]', 'adj.空运的；空中传播的；起飞后在飞行中', '1. Some doubt Kirlin can get them airborne. 有人怀疑柯林不可能把飞机空运过来。 2. The airborne forces however met hard fortune. 但是，空降部队遇到了不幸的命运。 3. There is no evidence that the disease is airborne. 目前并无证据显示疾病是由空气传播。 4. Using coke in iron ore reduction produces copious quantities of airborne particulates. 炼铁过程中使用焦炭，会在空中形成大量的悬浮粒子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overlap', '[ˌoʊvər\'læp]', 'vt.重叠；重复 vi.有重叠部分 n.重叠部分；重复', '1. A fish\'s scales overlap each other. 鱼鳞是一片片上下交叠起来的。 2. You need to overlap the pieces of wood slightly. 你需要把这些木片搭叠起来。 3. These two papers overlap in content. 这两篇论文有交叉的内容。 4. The programme has been so organized that none of the talks overlap. 日程做了精心安排，以使每一讲都没有重复内容。 5. Channel ranges must not overlap. 频道范围不能重叠。 6. There is a small overlap between the two circles. 在这两个圆周有一小部分重叠。', '过去式: overlapped 过去分词: overlapped 现在分词: overlapping 第三人称单数: overlaps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impact', '[\'ɪmpækt]', 'n.影响；冲击力；撞击 vt.挤入；压紧；撞击；对 ... 发生影响 vi.冲击；撞击；产生影响', '1. Seasonality or economic cycles will have minimal impact on secular trends. 季节性或经济周期两者对长期趋势的影响都不大。 2. But what these people fail to see is that international tourism may bring about a disastrous impact on our environment and local history. 但是这些人忽视了国际旅游可能会给当地环境和历史造成的灾难性的影响。 3. The impact of the crash hurtled the driver against the windshield of the car. 碰撞的震力使驾驶员猛撞于车子的挡风玻璃上。 4. The impact of the stone against the windowpane shattered the glass. 石头撞击窗户打碎了玻璃。 5. A vast crowd impacted the square. 广场上挤集了一大群人。 6. The company\'s performance was impacted by the high value of the pound. 公司的业绩受到了英镑高值的冲击。', '名词: impaction 过去式: impacted 过去分词: impacted 现在分词: impacting 第三人称单数: impacts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bask', '[bæsk]', 'vi.取暖；舒适地晒太阳；沐浴于', '1. Now we can bask in the rainbow of the memories that we\'ll nurture in the years ahead. 在未来岁月里，让我们在记忆的长虹里永远珍藏对他的怀念。 2. After his apprenticeship he worked for Joe Manton, the greatest gunsmith in England and a legend in his own lifetime. But James was not content to bask in anyone\'s reflected glory. 学徒期满后，詹姆士为英国最伟大的造枪巨子及其所在时代的一个传奇人物乔·曼顿工作。但是他并不愿意沾任何人的光。 3. I saw her basking in the sunshine. 我看到她在阳光下晒太阳。 4. We are basking on the beach. 我们在海滩上晒太阳。', '过去式: basked 过去分词: basked 现在分词: basking 第三人称单数: basks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cast', '[kæst]', 'v.掷；抛；投；铸造；指定演员；加起来；投射(目光)；投(票)；预测 n.演员阵容；投掷；[医]固定用敷料', '1. The angler cast her line into the stream. 那个垂钓者把鱼线掷进了小溪里。 2. The storm cast the little rowboat onto the rocks. 风暴把这条小划艇抛到岩石上。 3. The two world wars cast a shadow over the people all over the world. 两次世界大战在全世界人民中投下了阴影。 4. The metals most frequently cast are iron, steal, aluminum and so on. 最常用来铸造的金属是铁、钢、铝等。 5. The play succeeded thanks to the wonderful performance of all the cast. 由于演员们的精彩表演,这部戏获得了成功。', '过去式: cast 过去分词: cast 现在分词: casting 第三人称单数: casts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('captivate', '[\'kæptɪveɪt]', 'vt.迷住；迷惑', '1. He was captivated by her beauty. 他被她的美色迷住了。 2. The kindergarten children were captivated by the variety of animals in the zoo. 幼儿园的孩子们被动物园里的各种动物吸引住了。 3. The son is so captivate with the woman that he does not heed his parents\' warning. 儿子为这个女人神魂颠倒，全然不顾他父母的告诫。', '名词: captivation 过去式: captivated 过去分词: captivated 现在分词: captivating 第三人称单数: captivates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drought', '[draʊt]', 'n.干旱', '1. The long drought famished many people. 久旱使很多人陷入饥饿。 2. Famine is often the sequel to war or drought. 饥荒往往是战争或干旱造成的。 3. We have not enough food to eat because of the drought. 因为旱灾，我们没有足够的食物可吃。 4. The soil is cracking up because of the drought. 土地因干旱而正在龟裂。', '形容词: droughty 异体字: drouth');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('notwithstanding', '[ˌnɑːtwɪθ\'stændɪŋ]', 'adv.虽然；尽管 prep.纵使 conj.虽然', '1. He went, notwithstanding he was ordered to stay. 他虽被命令不许去，但还是去了。 2. Notwithstanding her naughtiness, I love my little girl. 尽管我的小姑娘很淘气，我还是很爱她。 3. Notwithstanding the bad weather, the match went on. 尽管天气很糟，比赛还是照常进行。 4. He still went home, notwithstanding the midnight. 尽管已近午夜，他还是回家去了。 5. Many people told me not to try, but I went ahead notwithstanding. 很多人都劝我不要尝试,我还是决意去做了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pretend', '[prɪ\'tend]', 'v.假装；装作；自以为', '1. She pretends that she likes them so that she can get their help. 她假装很喜欢他们，借以获得他们的帮助。 2. The young actor pretended to be Hamlet. 那个年轻演员扮演哈姆雷特。 3. She closed her eyes and pretended to be asleep. 她闭上眼睛,装作睡着了。 4. Surely he doesn\'t pretend to any understanding of music! 谅他不会自以为懂得什麽音乐吧！', '过去式: pretended 过去分词: pretended 现在分词: pretending 第三人称单数: pretends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exclude', '[ɪk\'skluːd]', 'vt.排除；阻止；拒绝接受', '1. At this stage we cannot entirely exclude the possibility of staff cuts. 在目前这个阶段,我们还不能完全排除裁员的可能性。 2. I mean the last thing we would think about is to exclude the children from this plan. 我的意思是,我们绝不会考虑把孩子们排除在这个计划之外的。 3. Thick curtains help to exclude street noises. 厚窗帘有助于隔绝街上的噪音。 4. The court excluded the improperly obtained evidence. 法院不接受非正常渠道获得的证据', '形容词: excludable 名词: excludability 过去式: excluded 过去分词: excluded 现在分词: excluding 第三人称单数: excludes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('silicon', '[\'sɪlɪkən]', 'n.硅', '1. Now people can produce a wafer silicon. 现在人们能够生产一种硅晶薄片。 2. Silicon is usually added by co-evaporation. 硅通常是通过共蒸发来加入的。 3. In computers, these diodes are primarily germanium or silicon crystals. 在计算机中,这些二极管基本上是锗或硅晶体二极管。', '简写符号: Si');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('surmount', '[sər\'maʊnt]', 'vt.克服；越过；登上 ... 最高点', '1. I think most of these obstacles can be surmounted. 我认为这些障碍大多数都是可以克服的。 2. We had many problems to surmount before we could start the project 我们得克服许多困难才能著手做这项工作. 3. The true love, should surmount the life the length, the mind width, the soul depth. 真正的爱，应该超越生命的长度、心灵的宽度、灵魂的深度。 4. I want to prove that sense can surmount impulse. 我要证明理智是可以战胜冲动的.', '形容词: surmountable 名词: surmounter 过去式: surmounted 过去分词: surmounted 现在分词: surmounting 第三人称单数: surmounts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alga', '[\'ælɡə]', 'n.海藻；水藻', '1. Some of the algae are edible. 有些藻类是可以吃的。 2. Alga was a good monitoring biology. 藻类是一个很好的测试生物。 3. Algae grow in water. 水藻生长在水中。 4. Alga was a good monitoring biology. 藻类是一个很好的测试生物。', '形容词: algal 名词复数: algae');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('calendar', '[\'kælɪndər]', 'n.日历；历法；日程表；一览表 vt.把 ... 列入日程表', '1. He tore a leaf from the calendar. 他从日历上撕下一页。 2. The other is the haab, or Calendar Round. 另外一个称为哈伯历，或者是历法圆周。 3. But this calendar also had problems. 可是这种历法也有问题。 4. I don\'t see how we can fit this into the mayor\'s busy calendar. 我不明白我们要怎样把这件事挤进市长满满的日程表中。 5. The assistant will calendar the next appointment in for me. 助手会把下一个会面排进我的日程表。', '过去式: calendared 过去分词: calendared 现在分词: calendaring 第三人称单数: calendars');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invitation', '[ˌɪnvɪ\'teɪʃn]', 'n.邀请；邀请函；招待；招致，引诱', '1. I appreciate your invitation. 感谢你的邀请。 2. He made a refusal to her invitation. 他拒绝了她的邀请。 3. Nobody in the office had received an invitation to the party. 在办公室里没有人收到邀请函去参加这个宴会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('academic', '[ˌækə\'demɪk]', 'adj.学院的；学术的；理论的 n.大学教师，大学生；学者，学究', '1. Sir Lawrence Alma-Tadema was an English painter in the academic tradition. 阿尔玛·台德玛是学院派的英国画家。 2. With my strong academic background, I am competent. 依我良好的学术背景,我能胜任。 3. Applicant must possess good conduct and obtain satisfactory academic results. 申请者必须拥有良好品性,并考获令人满意的成绩; 4. During the past four years I have had a good deal of academic experience in communications technology. 四年来,我掌握了丰富的通信技术上的理论知识。', '副词: academically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mythical', '[\'mɪθɪkl]', 'adj.神话的；虚构的；杜撰出来的', '1. Their wealth is merely mythical. 他们的财富完全是虚构的。 2. The artefact, made of gold, symbolises a mythical octopus with eight tentacles and a stylised human head displaying cat-like features. 这件由纯金制成的手工艺品绘有一只虚构的具有八只触角的章鱼，以及一个当地常见的看上去类似于猫的人头图案。', '副词: mythically 异体字: mythic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('encase', '[ɪn\'keɪs]', 'v.把...装入箱中；包起', '1. His broken leg was encased in plaster. 他折的腿打上了石膏。', '异体字: incase 名词: encasement 过去式: encased 过去分词: encased 现在分词: encasing 第三人称单数: encases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spectator', '[\'spekteɪtər]', 'n.观众；旁观者', '1. Baseball is largely a spectator sport. 棒球在很大程度上是一种观众型运动。 2. Many a spectator poured down the street to the football ground. 许多观众沿街向足球场走去。 3. Hanlei looks at the world as a spectator, waiting. 韩磊以一个旁观者的身份观察世界,他善于等待。 4. It is the spectator, and not life, that art really mirrors. 艺术所真正要反映的是旁观者，而不是生活。', '形容词: spectatorial 名词: spectatorship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('engraving', '[ɪn\'ɡreɪvɪŋ]', 'n.雕刻的画；镌版术；雕版 动词engrave的现在分词.', '1. I bought an old engraving of the High Street. 我买了一张“大街”的旧版画。 2. Go look in my office, you should find an engraving of a pentagram there. 到我的公务室来看，你能找到五角星形的雕塑。 3. This engraving of artistic work is sublime. No wonder it is so expensive. 这件艺术品的刻工十分精美，难怪会这么值钱。 4. Engraving printing is in vogue for a time from its invention to Song Dynasty. 雕版印刷发明后至两宋而盛极一时。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comparative', '[kəm\'pærətɪv]', 'adj.比较的；相当的 n.比较级', '1. He majored in comparative literature. 他的专业是比较文学。 2. To illustrate my point I have done a comparative analysis. 为说明我的观点，我做了对比分析。 3. The expedition was a comparative success. 那次探险相当成功。 4. He is a comparative stranger in our impression. 在我们的印象中他是个相当陌生的人。 5. \"Worse\" is the comparative of \"bad\". \"worse\"是\"bad\"的比较级。', '副词: comparatively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('catastrophe', '[kə\'tæstrəfi]', 'n.大灾难；大祸；彻底失败', '1. The earthquake was a terrible catastrophe. 这次地震是个可怕的灾难。 2. He is teetering on the edge of catastrophe. 他在大灾难的边缘徘徊。 3. The catastrophe would be stamped in their minds. 那场灾难将会深深地印在他们的头脑里。 4. Their other problems paled into insignificance beside this latest catastrophe. 最近发生这一灾祸后,他们其他的问题都显得无关重要了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('canvas', '[\'kænvəs]', 'n.油画；帆布；（帆布）画布', '1. The artist showed me his canvases. 画家给我看了他的油画。 2. He bought the canvas for ten thousand dollars. 他以一万美元买下这幅油画。 3. The hole was covered (over) with canvas. 这个洞被帆布遮盖住了。 4. The plumber stowed all his gear in a canvas bag. 管子工把他所有的工具都装进一只帆布袋里。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forth', '[fɔːrθ]', 'adv.向前；向外；露出', '1. The guard walked back and forth in front of the gate. 警卫在大门前走来走去。 2. He went forth into the desert to pray 他向前走到沙漠中祈祷。 3. Suddenly oil sprang forth from the pipe. 油突然从管子里喷了出来。 4. The trees burst forth in spring. 树木在春天开始抽芽。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dentist', '[\'dentɪst]', 'n.牙科医生', '1. The dentist told the boy not to eat too many sweets. 牙医告诫这男孩不要吃太多糖果。 2. I have an appointment with my dentist this afternoon. 我已约好今天下午去看牙医。 3. The dentist took out his bad tooth yesterday. 昨天医生拔掉了他的一颗坏牙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spot', '[spɑːt]', 'n.地点；场所；职位；污点；斑点；少量；聚光灯；插播节目 adj.现场的；现货的；插播的 v.（使）产生污渍；玷污；认出；用灯光照射', '1. This is the spot where the two trucks collided. 这儿就是两辆卡车相撞的地点。 2. That was the common spot for settling affairs of honour. 那是他们通常决斗的场所。 3. She found a spot as a secretary. 她找到一个秘书的职位。 4. He flicked at spot with handkerchief. 他轻轻地用手帕拂拭污点。 5. Several television stations gave spot coverage to the conference. 好几家电视台对大会作了现场报导。 6. His boots were spotted with mud. 他的靴子上沾有泥渍。', '形容词: spottable 过去式: spotted 过去分词: spotted 现在分词: spotting 第三人称单数: spots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('belt', '[belt]', 'n.腰带；带状物；地带；皮带 vt.用皮带抽打；用带系上；用带标示 vi.疾驰；大声歌唱', '1. He has a brown belt in karate. 他有一条空手道的棕腰带。（他是空手道茶带） 2. A belt of trees grew between the two fields. 两块田之间有一条树木带。 3. As Indonesia lies in the volcanic belt, earthquakes can occur. 由于印尼位于火山地带,因此有发生地震的可能。 4. My trousers only stay up if I wear a belt. 我这条裤子要是不系皮带就往下掉。 5. He strapped the driver with a leather belt. 他用皮带抽打司机。 6. They went belting along the road. 他们沿着马路疾驰而去。', '过去式: belted 过去分词: belted 现在分词: belting 第三人称单数: belts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agreeable', '[ə\'ɡriːəbl]', 'adj.愉快的；和蔼可亲的；欣然同意的；一致的', '1. I enjoyed an agreeable holiday this summer. 今年夏天我度过了一个愉快的假期。 2. We spent a most agreeable day together. 我们在一起度过了非常愉快的一天。 3. I find her a very agreeable woman. 我发现她是个和蔼可亲的女人。 4. To a more agreeable adviser, or one from whom he would be more likely to learn, Mr. Harthouse could never be recommended. 赫德豪士先生表示谁也不能给他介绍一位更和蔼可亲的顾问，或者他会更可能向之学习的顾问了。', '副词: agreeably 名词: agreeability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('theoretical', '[ˌθiːə\'retɪkl]', 'adj.理论上的', '1. These findings have both theoretical and practical applications. 这些发现具有理论和实际的应用。 2. Theoretical study must be closely integrated with practice. 理论学习要紧密结合实际。 3. It\'s a theoretical possibility, but I don\'t suppose it will happen. 这是一种理论上的可能性，但我认为这种情况不会发生。', '副词: theoretically 异体字: theoretic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('greasy', '[\'ɡriːsi]', 'adj.油腻的；滑溜溜的；油滑的', '1. His greasy hair repelled her. 他头发油腻很讨她嫌。 2. Impregnated, smeared with, or containing oil; greasy. 充满油的，涂了油的，含油的; 油腻的 3. A greasy hamburger. 油腻的汉堡包 4. The greasy food make her feel sick. 油腻的食物令她恶心。', '副词: greasily 比较级: greasier 最高级: greasiest 名词: greasiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fuse', '[fjuːz]', 'n.保险丝；导火线；引线 vt.熔化；融合；装导线；装引信于 vi.熔化；融合', '1. The fuse-box is in the kitchen. 保险丝盒子在厨房里。 2. Changing a fuse is one of those fiddly jobs I hate. 我最不愿意干换保险丝这类活儿了。 3. It seems that you\'ve blown a fuse. 看样子你把保险丝烧断了。 4. I know how to mend a fuse and I don\'t need you shoving your oar in! 我知道怎麽弄保险丝，用不著你管！ 5. We fuse copper and tin to make bronze. 我们把铜和锡熔制成青铜。 6. The metal will fuse at a relatively low temperature. 这金属在不太高的温度下熔化。', '过去式: fused/fuzed 过去分词: fused/fuzed 现在分词: fusing/fuzing 第三人称单数: fuses/fuzes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('antique', '[æn\'tiːk]', 'adj.古代的；古老的；过时的 n.古董；古物', '1. The antique table went to the lady in the pink hat. 这张古董桌子卖给那位戴粉红色帽子的女士了。 2. In the museum we saw many antique plates. 我们在博物馆看到了很多古时候的盘子. 3. The antique furniture was made in 1700. 这件古老的家具是1700年制造的。 4. She wore an antique gown to the costume party. 她穿着一件过时的长袍参加化妆舞会。 5. The value of that antique is inestimable. 那件古董的价值无法估计。', '副词: antiquely 名词: antiqueness 过去式: antiqued 过去分词: antiqued 现在分词: antiquing 第三人称单数: antiques');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('respect', '[rɪ\'spekt]', 'vt.尊敬；尊重；遵守；关于；涉及 n.尊敬；敬重；关系；方面 n.（复）respects: 敬意；问候', '1. All students should respect their teachers. 凡是学生就应当尊敬老师。 2. I respected their moral standards. 我尊重他们的道德标准。 3. I respect him as a writer and as a man. 我尊重他这位作家，也尊重他这个人。 4. We must respect the laws of a country we are in. 我们必须遵守所在国家的法律。 5. The students have great respect for their history teacher. 学生们非常尊敬他们的历史老师。 6. We called to pay our respects. 我们去拜望了，以表示敬意', '名词: respecter 过去式: respected 过去分词: respected 现在分词: respecting 第三人称单数: respects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('artisan', '[\'ɑːrtəzn]', 'n.工匠；技工', '1. He is an artisan in leatherwork. 他是个皮匠。 2. The vase made by the artisan is wonderful. 那个手艺人做的花瓶棒极了。 3. The artisan crafted a set of complicated tools. 这名匠人设计了一套复杂的工具。 4. He was a man of lofty stature, half peasant, half artisan. 他是一个身材高大,一副半农半工的模样。', '名词: artisanship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mount', '[maʊnt]', 'v.登上；爬上；装上；上升 n.底板；爬上；支架；乘用马 n.山；峰', '1. He mounted the horse and rode off. 他骑上马走了。 2. Be careful not to mount the pavement when you\'re parking the car. 你停车时,小心不要停上人行道。 3. The frame on desk can make independent shelf already, also can conveniently mount. 书桌上的架子既能成为独立的书架,也能方便地装上。 4. His debts continued to mount up. 他的债务在不断增长。 5. The general had an excellent mount. 将军有出色的坐骑。 6. Mount Jolmo Lungma is the highest mountain in the world. 珠穆朗玛峰是世界上最高的山峰。', '形容词: mountable 名词: mounter 过去式: mounted 过去分词: mounted 现在分词: mounting 第三人称单数: mounts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('specialize', '[\'speʃəlaɪz]', 'v.专攻', '1. This shop specializes in chocolates. 这个商店专门出售巧克力。 2. He specializes in oriental history. 他专门研究东方史。 3. I specialize in the sale of cotton piece goods. May I act as your agent? 我专营棉布买卖，我可作为你们的代理吗？ 4. \"A science fiction cannot not be regarded as a mere entertainment, but in fact it tells the reader much more.\" \"科幻小说不能简单地看成是供消遣的，而实际上它给读者展示更深刻的内容。\"', '过去式: specialized 过去分词: specialized 现在分词: specializing 第三人称单数: specializes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gale', '[ɡeɪl]', 'n.狂风；一阵（喧闹；笑声等）', '1. The gale blew down the flagstaff. 狂风把旗杆吹倒了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('passion', '[\'pæʃn]', 'n.激情；热情；酷爱；盛怒', '1. The dying embers of the former passion can still be seen in his articles. 往日激情将熄的余烬仍可从他的文章中看出来。 2. Life needs curiosity, enthusiasm and passion, which depends on how we think of the world. 生活需要好奇心、热情和激情,这都取决于我们怎么看待这个世界。 3. I have a passion for American literature. 我酷爱美国文学。 4. His passion for reading never deserted him. 他从未放弃过对读书的热爱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idiot', '[\'ɪdiət]', 'n.白痴；傻瓜；笨蛋', '1. What a stupid idiot! 真是个愚蠢的白痴！ 2. I didn\'t mince matters: I said he was an idiot. 我不讳言，我说过他是白痴。 3. He\'s a ruddy idiot. 他是个大傻瓜。 4. Don\'t treat me as if I were an idiot. 别把我当傻瓜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('harsh', '[hɑːrʃ]', 'adj.粗糙的；严厉的，严酷的；刺耳的；使人不舒服的；大约的', '1. Yorke himself has a harsh face. 约克本人长着张粗糙的脸。 2. The punishment was too harsh for him. 这种惩罚对他来说太严厉了。 3. He had deliberately made his voice harsh. 他故意嘶哑着嗓门。', '副词: harshly 比较级: harsher 最高级: harshest 名词: harshness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consider', '[kən\'sɪdər]', 'v.考虑；思考；认为；体谅；注视', '1. Please take time to consider the problem. 请仔细考虑一下这个问题。 2. They did not consider whether they could afford the time or not. 他们没有考虑是否抽得出时间。 3. When you read, don\'t just consider what the author thinks, consider what you think. 当你在阅读的时候,不要只是思考作者在想什么,而是要思考你在想什么。 4. We consider that the driver is not to blame. 我们认为这不是司机的过错。', '名词: consideration 过去式: considered 过去分词: considered 现在分词: considering 第三人称单数: considers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gallop', '[\'ɡæləp]', 'n.疾驰；飞奔 v.飞驰；急速进行', '1. The horse went off at a gallop across the field. 那匹马疾驰起来跑过田野。 2. All the horses broke into a gallop. 所有的马突然飞奔起来。 3. The donkey began to trot faster , then to gallop. 驴开始跑得快起来了，然后飞奔。 4. Two people gallop whip and spur, do not come in the city a little while. 两人快马加鞭飞驰，不一会儿就来到城里。', '名词: galloper 过去式: galloped 过去分词: galloped 现在分词: galloping 第三人称单数: gallops');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('axis', '[\'æksɪs]', 'n.轴；中枢', '1. The earth turns (ie rotates) on its axis once every 24 hours. 地球每24小时自转一圈。 2. A wheel revolves round/on its axis. 轮子是绕轴旋转的。 3. The earth\'s axis is the line between the North and South Poles. 地轴是南北极之间的线。 4. The axis of a circle is its diameter. 圆的轴线是其直径。', '名词复数: axes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glide', '[ɡlaɪd]', 'v.滑动；滑翔；溜走 n.滑动；滑过；滑音', '1. The figure skater glided gracefully over the ice. 花样滑冰者在冰上优雅地滑行。 2. The swans glide gracefully on the lake. 天鹅在湖的上空优美地滑翔。 3. The plane managed to glide down to the runway. 飞机终于成功地滑翔降落在跑道上。 4. He glide away from the classroom. 他溜出教室。 5. When a word ends in a vowel sound and the next word begins with a vowel sound, they are connected with a glide between the two vowels. 如果一个单词以元音结束，下一个单词以元音开始的话，两个元音之间用一个滑音连在一起。', '过去式: glided 过去分词: glided 现在分词: gliding 第三人称单数: glides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recluse', '[\'rekluːs]', 'n.隐士', '1. This recluse shunned all company. 这位隐士不与任何人来往。 2. All these years, Eric had lived as a recluse. 这些年来，埃里克都是过着隐士生活。 3. She can\'t just be written off as an eccentric recluse. 不能仅仅把她当成一个古怪的隐居者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anomaly', '[ə\'nɑːməli]', 'n.异常；反常；不规则', '1. A cat with no tail is an anomaly. 没尾巴的猫是一只畸形猫。 2. NASA\'s system for tracking anomalies for flight readiness reviews failed. 在飞行准备阅兵式中，美国航空及太空总署的异常情况追踪系统失败了。 3. In those days, a woman professor was still an anomaly. 当时，女教授仍然是一种反常现象。 4. This should probably be considered an annoying anomaly rather than anything more significant. 这应该可能被看作是一个讨厌的不规则而非任何更有意义的事。', '形容词: anomalistic 副词: anomalistically 名词复数: anomalies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unparalleled', '[ʌn\'pærəleld]', 'adj.无比的；无双的；空前的', '1. It was an unparalleled opportunity to develop her career. 这是她发展自己的事业的绝好机会。 2. The recent economic recession is unparalleled since the 1930s. 最近的经济不景气是自三十年代以来最严重的一次。 3. The book has enjoyed a success unparalleled in recent publishing history. 这本书在近期出版史上是空前的成功。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bureau', '[\'bjʊroʊ]', 'n.局；办事处；(带抽屉的）写字台', '1. He works in this bureau. 他在这个局工作过。 2. The travel bureau is not so far from here. 旅游局离这里不远。 3. He worked in a travel bureau. 他在一家旅行社工作。 4. He picked up that bureau at a second-hand store. 这个柜子是他在一家旧货店买的。', '名词复数: bureaus');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frank', '[fræŋk]', 'adj.坦白的；直率的；真诚的 vt.免费邮寄；使自由出入 n.免费邮寄；弗兰克（人名）', '1. A frank discussion can help to clear the air. 坦率的谈论有助于消除疑虑。 2. To be very frank, I think you have very little chance of getting the job. 坦白地说，我认为你获得这项工作的机会微乎其微。 3. He was frank, open and aboveboard. 他胸怀坦白，光明磊落。 4. They tend to be frank and open but alo self-centered and willful. 他们的性格坦诚、直率，但往往以自我为中心，并且任性妄为。 5. We are trying to frank him through customs. 我们正努力使他免检通过海关。', '比较级: franker 最高级: frankest 名词: frankness 过去式: franked 过去分词: franked 现在分词: franking 第三人称单数: franks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('substance', '[\'sʌbstəns]', 'n.实质；物质；财产；内容；重要性', '1. The Substance and Prospect of \"East China Sea\" Dispute between China and Japan 中日\"东海问题\"的实质及展望 2. The emery is a hard metallic substance. 金刚砂是非常坚硬的金属物质。 3. Beware of what you do with this dangerous substance. 你处理这些危险品时，可要当心。 4. Later he became a man of substance. 后来，他成为颇具资产的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intricate', '[\'ɪntrɪkət]', 'adj.复杂的；难懂的', '1. It was an intricate and ingenious system. 这是一个复杂而精致的体系。 2. The prisoners designed the intricate escape. 囚犯们策划了那起周密的越狱事件。 3. Taiwan is a complex of intricate relationships. 台湾是个各种关系错综复杂的地方。 4. The situation seems to be intricate. 局势似乎错综复杂。', '副词: intricately 名词: intricateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hump', '[hʌmp]', 'n.驼背；圆形隆起物；土墩；肿块；碰撞；恼火 v.使隆起；碰撞；敲击成圆丘形；弓起', '1. So does he have a hump and a hairpiece? 他既驼背又带假发？ 2. That gives me the hump. 那使我心烦。 3. I\'ve got the hump over what he said to me. 我已经对他所说的很不耐烦了。 4. A cat often humps its back. 猫常弓起背部。', '形容词: humped 过去式: humped 过去分词: humped 现在分词: humping 第三人称单数: humps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insight', '[\'ɪnsaɪt]', 'n.洞察力；见识；深刻的理解', '1. I\'ve got an insight into the problem. 我对问题豁然开朗。 2. The book is filled with remarkable insights. 这本书很有真知卓见。 3. In this new book he hits off the American temperament with amazing insight. 在这本新书里，他对美国人性格的描写表现出惊人的洞察力。 4. Once human limits are breached, the person sees beyond the horizon of human insight, to reach a truly cosmic consciousness. 当局限被打破,人们的洞察力就可以超越凡人,看到宇宙真正的奥秘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frail', '[freɪl]', 'adj.脆弱的；虚弱的', '1. I will not torment the emotionally frail. 我再也不折磨情感脆弱的人了。 2. Jail life made the frail retailer avail every snail in the pail. 监狱生命使脆弱的零售商在桶里有益于每只蜗牛。 3. His frail hands could hardly hold a cup. 他虚弱的手连杯子也拿不住。 4. This frail child did not survive. 这个身体虚弱的孩子没能活下来。', '副词: frailly 比较级: frailer 最高级: frailest 名词: frailness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hybrid', '[\'haɪbrɪd]', 'n.混合物；杂种；混血儿 adj.杂种的；混合的', '1. The music was a hybrid of western pop and traditional folk song. 这种音乐融合了西方流行音乐和传统民歌。 2. A mule is a hybrid of a donkey and a horse. 骡子是公驴和母马交配而生的杂种。 3. She is a hybrid of the African and the Chinese. 她是中非混血儿。 4. He is interested in hybrid animals. 他对杂交产生的动物感兴趣。', '名词: hybridism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hoist', '[hɔɪst]', 'v.升起；升高；举起 n.起重机；升高', '1. They hoist cargo with a locomobile crane. 他们用自动推进的起重机吊起货物。', '名词: hoister 过去式: hoisted 过去分词: hoisted 现在分词: hoisting 第三人称单数: hoists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spin', '[spɪn]', 'v.(使)旋转；疾驰；纺织；结网；眩晕 n.纺织；旋转；眩晕；疾驰', '1. My sister can spin on her toes like a dancer. 我妹妹能像舞者一样踮着脚尖旋转。 2. The motorcycles were spinning along at full speed. 摩托车正全速疾驰。 3. Mother used to spin her own yarn. 母亲过去一直是自己纺纱的。 4. In spring, they spin their cocoons. 到了春天，它们才吐丝结茧。 5. Before the invention of spin technology, zoic fur were mainly material. 在纺织技术尚未发明之前，动物的毛皮是人们服装的主要材料。', '过去式: spun/span 过去分词: spun 现在分词: spinning 第三人称单数: spins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('joint', '[dʒɔɪnt]', 'adj.联合的；共同的；连带的；合资的 n.关节；接头；接合处；接缝；夜总会 v.贴合；连接', '1. They covenanted with us for establishing a joint venture. 他们就建立合资公司的事和我们签了合约。 2. In this contract, Board shall mean the board of director of the joint venture . 在本合同中，board指的是本合资企业的董事会。 3. These foreigners have put forward a proposal for a joint venture. 这些外国人提出了一个合资企业的建议。 4. The joint isn\'t quite done yet. 这一大块肉煮得不太熟。 5. Does any one know who can joint sales calls? 谁知道谁可以做联合销售拜访?', '过去式: jointed 过去分词: jointed 现在分词: jointing 第三人称单数: joints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('warn', '[wɔːrn]', 'vt.警告；告诫；预先通知 vi.发出警告', '1. He warned me against going there at night. 他警告我晚上不要到那去。 2. They warn her that if she do it again she will be sent to prison. 他们警告她说她再这么干就把她关进监狱。 3. The police warn us not to go out at night. 警察告诫我们夜间不要出门。 4. I warned them that there might be snakes in the woods. 我提醒他们树林里可能有蛇。 5. Birds sometimes chatter to each other to warn of danger. 鸟儿有时互相啁啾,通报危险。', '名词: warner 过去式: warned 过去分词: warned 现在分词: warning 第三人称单数: warns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emission', '[i\'mɪʃn]', 'n.散发；发行；排放', '1. In addition, wetland soils are known for methane emission, a greenhouse gas. 此外,湿地散发沼气这种温室气体,是人所共知的。 2. The limitless emission of foreign currencies has an serious influence on the country\'s economy. 外汇的无限制发行严重影响了该国的经济。 3. New regulations are aimed at reducing the vehicle emission. 新规定的目的是要降低汽车尾气的排放。 4. Emission of smoke from chimneys is an offense. 在这里排放烟雾是违法的事情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aggravate', '[\'æɡrəveɪt]', 'vt.恶化；严重', '1. Scratching can aggravate the rash. 搔痒会使疹子发炎。 2. The Europeans\' appeasement policy towards irrational regimes would only aggravate the hidden dangers. 欧洲国家对非理性政权的绥靖政策,只会让潜在危机恶化。 3. This will aggravate the current scarcity of natural resources caused by environmental degradation. 这将会加剧由环境恶化而导致的自然资源匮乏的情况。 4. The lack of rain aggravated the already serious shortage of food. 干旱少雨使原本就很严重的粮食短缺问题更加严重。', '形容词: aggravative 副词: aggravatingly 名词: aggravator 过去式: aggravated 过去分词: aggravated 现在分词: aggravating 第三人称单数: aggravates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('empty', '[\'empti]', 'adj.空的；空洞的；空虚的；空腹的 v.倒空；变空；排空 n.空物', '1. His room is empty. 他的房间是空的。 2. His wordy and empty speech was a frost. 他的冗长空洞的讲话使人厌烦。 3. He didn\'t want to retire and lead an empty life. 他不想退休过空虚的生活。 4. This medicine must be taken on an empty stomach. 这种药必须空腹服用。 5. They emptied the biscuits onto the plate. 他们把饼干倒在盘子里。 6. Empties are not taken back. 不退瓶子。', '副词: emptily 比较级: emptier 最高级: emptiest 名词: emptiness 名词复数: empties 过去式: emptied 过去分词: emptied 现在分词: emptying 第三人称单数: empties');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delta', '[\'deltə]', 'n.(河流的)三角洲；希腊语第四个字母（Δ、δ）', '1. There are fertile fields in the Nile Delta. 尼罗河三角洲土地肥沃。 2. They were the terror of the Ganges delta. 他们已成为恒河三角洲的令人胆寒的力量。', '形容词: deltaic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flexible', '[\'fleksəbl]', 'adj.柔韧的；灵活的；易弯曲的；可变通的', '1. This tube is flexible but tough. 这管子柔软但很坚固。 2. We need a foreign policy that is more flexible. 我们需要一个更为灵活的外交政策。 3. People use Java because it is flexible and runs on multiple platforms. 人们使用Java是因为它的灵活性及在多种平台上可以运行。 4. Leather and rubber are flexible, glass and iron are not. 皮革和橡胶都是易弯曲的，玻璃和铁则不然。', '副词: flexibly 名词: flexibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('locally', '[\'ləʊkəli]', 'adv.在本地；地方性地；局部地', '1. We recruit all our restaurant staff locally . 我们从本地招所有的餐厅职员。 2. This is all locally grown produce. 这都是本地农产品。 3. How is he regarded locally? 当地的人对他看法如何? 4. Meetings were held locally and nationally. 举行的会议有地方性的，有全国性的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genetics', '[dʒə\'netɪks]', 'n.遗传学', '1. Genetics is beyond my scope. 遗传学不是我的专长。 2. Charaka also knew the fundamentals of genetics. 查拉卡也知道遗传学的基本原理。 3. In genetics, genes were formerly called factors. 在遗传学上，基因以前被称为遗传因子。 4. This week, we look back at a major discovery in genetics. 这周，我们来回顾一下遗传学中的主要表现。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outrageous', '[aʊt\'reɪdʒəs]', 'adj.过分的；骇人的', '1. The price is outrageous. 价钱高得吓人。 2. The princess spent an outrageous amount on clothes. 公主在穿着上挥霍无度。 3. She didn\'t even blink at his outrageous proposal. 她对他蛮横的求婚一点儿也不感到惊讶。 4. Some of his suggestions verged on the outrageous. 他的一些建议都快到了荒唐的地步。', '副词: outrageously 名词: outrageousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('restore', '[rɪ\'stɔːr]', 'vt.恢复；归还；复原', '1. The military government promised to restore democracy within one year. 军人政府答应在一年内重新建立民主体制。 2. Drastic measures will have to be taken to restore order. 为恢复秩序必须采取严厉措施。 3. The police must try to restore order. 警方必须努力恢复治安。 4. The new manager\'s job is to restore the company to profitability. 新经理的工作是让这家公司能恢复盈利状况。', '名词: restorer 过去式: restored 过去分词: restored 现在分词: restoring 第三人称单数: restores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sneer', '[snɪr]', 'n.冷笑；嘲笑 v.嘲笑；冷笑', '1. Ambreene favored him with a disbelieving sneer. 艾布瑞妮回以一个不相信的冷笑。 2. Defiance gleamed in Casey\'s eye, a sneer curled Casey\'s lip. 轻蔑在凯西眼中闪现，冷笑在凯西唇边出现。 3. The remark was, of course, a sneer. 这话当然是一种嘲笑。 4. It\'s not polite to jeer or sneer. 嘲笑别人是不礼貌的。 5. The remark was, of course, a sneer. 这话当然是一种嘲笑。', '形容词: sneerful 副词: sneeringly 名词: sneerer 过去式: sneered 过去分词: sneered 现在分词: sneering 第三人称单数: sneers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('effect', '[ɪ\'fekt]', 'n.效应；结果；影响；印象；效果；要旨 v.使产生；引起', '1. The aspirins soon took effect. 服下的阿司匹林药片很快见效了。 2. The advertising campaign didn\'t have much effect on sales. 这些广告攻势对销售额并没有起到多大作用。 3. What is certain is that every effect must have a cause. 每一个结果都有一个原因，这是确定无疑的 4. This will have a negligible effect on the temperature. 这对温度的影响将是微乎其微的。 5. Doctors cannot effect a cure if the disease has spread too far. 假如这种疾病已扩散得厉害，医生也无法妙手回春。', '形容词: effectible 名词: effecter 过去式: effected 过去分词: effected 现在分词: effecting 第三人称单数: effects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stab', '[stæb]', 'v.刺；戳；刺伤 n.刺；戳；刺痛；尝试', '1. Good friends stab you in the front. 当面刺痛你的是你的好朋友。 2. He stabbed at the earth with his stick. 他拿手杖戳著地。 3. She stabbed at the air with her finger to emphasize what she was saying. 她手指一戳一戳的，强调她说的话。 4. He stabbed the meat with his fork/stabbed his fork into the meat. 他用叉子叉肉。 5. The hunter made a stab at the wolf, but missed. 猎人向狼刺去，但没有刺中。', '名词: stabber 过去式: stabbed 过去分词: stabbed 现在分词: stabbing 第三人称单数: stabs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detract', '[dɪ\'trækt]', 'vi.减损 vt.转移', '1. His bad manners detract from his good character. 他的不礼貌减损了他的品质。 2. Pointing fingers will merely take up more time and detract from the argument for practicality. 用手指指向对方只会浪费更多的时间，并减损实用性的根据。', '名词: detractor 过去式: detracted 过去分词: detracted 现在分词: detracting 第三人称单数: detracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('locality', '[loʊ\'kæləti]', 'n.地区；位置；地点；方位', '1. There are several supermarkets in the locality. 这个地区有好几家超市。 2. Public transport is a big problem in this locality. 公共交通是这个地区的大问题。 3. People in this locality used to take two meals a day. 这儿的居民过去每天吃两餐饭。 4. They are trying to pinpoint the ship\'s exact locality. 他们正在设法确定轮船的确切位置。', '名词复数: localities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('undo', '[ʌn\'duː]', 'v.解开；松开；取消', '1. Would you please undo this knot for me? 你能不能帮我把这个结解开？ 2. He tried to undo the knot by picking at it with his fingers. 他用手指不停地扯，想把绳结解开。 3. To return a database to its state as of the last committed change, i.e., to undo recent uncommitted changes. 使一个数据库返回到它上次已确认的改变之后的状态，即取消最近的尚未确认的变动。 4. A compensating transaction means that a new transaction will undo the effects of previous transactions. 补偿事务的意思是一个新事物会用于取消前一个事务的所有效果。', '名词: undoer 过去式: undid 过去分词: undone 现在分词: undoing 第三人称单数: undoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('profoundly', '[prə\'faʊndli]', 'adv.深深地；深刻地', '1. His feeling has been harmed profoundly. 他的感情被深深地伤害了。 2. Hari was profoundly moved and shed tears. 哈里被深深地感动了，流下了眼泪。 3. Culture can profoundly influence gene frequencies in a population. 文化能深刻地影响群体中的基因频率。 4. This kind of unique self- valueconcern profoundly infected the cainozoic era. 这种独特的自我价值关怀深刻地感染了新生代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('originate', '[ə\'rɪdʒɪneɪt]', 'v.发起；开始；起源于；[计算机] 起始', '1. They originated the plan. 他们首先提出这一计划。 2. Who originated the concept of stereo sound? 立体声是谁发明的？ 3. And how did this peculiar custom originate? 而且，这种奇特的习俗又是怎么开始的呢? 4. The quarrel originated in rivalry between the two families. 这次争吵是两家不和引起的。', '形容词: originative 副词: originatively 名词: origination 过去式: originated 过去分词: originated 现在分词: originating 第三人称单数: originates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embarrass', '[ɪm\'bærəs]', 'vt.使窘迫；使尴尬；使为难 vi.窘迫', '1. She dragged up that incident just to embarrass me. 她又扯起那件事故意想使我难堪。 2. He was embarrassed by many debts. 他被很多债务弄得焦灼不安。 3. She may embarrass you with her uncouth behavior. 她的粗野行为可能会让你尴尬。 4. You didn\'t embarrass me in the slightest. 你一点也没让我为难。 5. Eye contact may convey sincerity and attentiveness in Western cultures but too much eye contact may embarrass people in some Oriental cultures. 在西方文化，目光接触能传递真诚和关注，但太多的目光接触在某些东方文化中则令人窘迫。', '副词: embarrassedly 过去式: embarrassed 过去分词: embarrassed 现在分词: embarrassing 第三人称单数: embarrasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kingdom', '[\'kɪŋdəm]', 'n.王国；领域；界 Kingdom：天国.', '1. The ruler of a kingdom is designated a king. 王国的统治者称作国王。 2. The Calcite Mineral Kingdom addresses you today. 今天是方解石王国向你们问候。 3. This is the fight of the kingdom of the mind. 这是思想领域的斗争。 4. Language was considered a specific sphere, a fourth natural kingdom. 人们把语言看作一种特殊的领域，自然界的第四王国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('radar', '[\'reɪdɑːr]', 'n.雷达', '1. There are enemy aircraft on the radar screen. 雷达萤屏上出现了敌人的飞机。 2. They plotted aircraft movements by radar. 他们借雷达标示飞机的动向。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disguise', '[dɪs\'ɡaɪz]', 'vt.掩饰；假装；假扮 n.伪装；伪装物', '1. She could not disguise her amusement at his mistake. 她对他的错误忍俊不禁。 2. It proved difficult to disguise his anxiety. 他的焦虑难以掩饰。 3. She disguised herself as a man, but she couldn\'t disguise her voice. 她把自己乔装成一个男子，但她改变不了自己的声音。 4. He plans to disguise himself as a policeman. 他打算把自己假扮成一个警察。 5. The supposed beggar was really a police officer in disguise. 那个众人眼中的乞丐，其实是化了装的警察。', '副词: disguisedly 名词: disguisement 过去式: disguised 过去分词: disguised 现在分词: disguising 第三人称单数: disguises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revival', '[rɪ\'vaɪvl]', 'n.复兴；复活；恢复精神', '1. This method is now undergoing a slow revival. 目前这种方法正在慢慢复兴。 2. The causes of this revival were many and complex. 这次复兴的原因是复杂多样的。 3. Life is a continuous course of death and revival. 生命是连续不断的死亡与复活。 4. We oppose the revival of militarism. 我们反对军国主义的复活。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('veto', '[\'viːtoʊ]', 'n.否决；否决权 v.否决', '1. Will they interpose their veto again? 他们还会再次否决吗? 2. An abstention is not regarded as a veto. 弃权不视为否决。 3. Mr Bush\'s veto does not kill stem-cell research. 布什的否决没有彻底封杀干细胞研究。 4. They carried the ministerial veto. 他们行使了内阁否决权。 5. The president last week vetoed the tax cut. 总统上个星期否决了减税法案。', '名词: vetoer 名词复数: vetoes 过去式: vetoed 过去分词: vetoed 现在分词: vetoing 第三人称单数: vetoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dignify', '[\'dɪɡnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使高贵；使增辉；抬高…的身价；将…美其名为', '1. Dignified in conduct or appearance. 高贵的行为、相貌显得高贵的 2. The broad steps in front of the mansion made it look very dignified. 宽阔的台阶使大厦的正面显得很气派。', '过去式: dignified 过去分词: dignified 现在分词: dignifying 第三人称单数: dignifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embellish', '[ɪm\'belɪʃ]', 'v.美化、装饰或修饰；渲染或添枝加叶', '1. We embellish our room with new rug, lamp, and picture. 我们以新地毯，灯和图画布置我们的房间。 2. My daughter wears a dress embellished with lace and ribbons today. 今天我女儿穿了一件有花边和饰带的连衣裙。 3. Nothing can embellish a beautiful face more than a narrow band drawn over the brow. 除了一条横束额上的细带而外，没有别的东西能把美丽的面庞衬托得更好的了。 4. He often embellishes the tales of his travels. 他常给他的旅游趣闻添枝加叶。', '名词: embellisher 过去式: embellished 过去分词: embellished 现在分词: embellishing 第三人称单数: embellishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('orbit', '[\'ɔːrbɪt]', 'n.势力范围；眼眶；轨迹 vt.绕轨道而行；进入轨道 vi.盘旋', '1. Hou Kou district fell into Japanese orbit before the outbreak of the second sino-Japan war. 虹口区在抗日战争爆发前就已落入日本人手中。 2. In the right orbit, an external ethmoidectomy was done, while in the left, a transnasal endoscopic approach was used to remove the inferomedial wall. 两边皆以外侧眼眶切开术行外侧眼窝减压术合并内侧及部分眼窝底减压术。 3. Conclusions For patients undergoing enophthalmos caused by a crepitant frature in orbit, it is the best way to perform an operation as early as possible. 结论对于眼眶爆裂性骨折引起的眼球内陷可考虑早期手术，其效果优于晚期手术者。 4. The spacecraft is in orbit around the moon. 该航天器在绕月球轨道运行。 5. The space shuttle will orbit a weather satellite. 太空梭将把一个气象卫星送入运行轨道。 6. Make one more orbit to the left again. 左转弯再盘旋一圈。', '过去式: orbited 过去分词: orbited 现在分词: orbiting 第三人称单数: orbits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exceed', '[ɪk\'siːd]', 'vt.超过；超出 vi.领先', '1. His knowledge of history exceeds mine. 他的历史知识超过我。 2. Demand began to exceed supply. 开始供不应求。 3. The fine shall not exceed $300. 罚款不超过三百美元。', '过去式: exceeded 过去分词: exceeded 现在分词: exceeding 第三人称单数: exceeds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devour', '[dɪ\'vaʊər]', 'v.吞食；毁灭；贪婪地阅读', '1. He sat by the fire, devouring beef and onions. 他坐在火炉旁，狼吞虎咽地吃着牛肉和洋葱。 2. We watched the flames devour the entire building. 我们看着火苗吞噬整座大楼。 3. The child devours fairy tales. 这孩子专注地听着童话故事。', '副词: devouringly 名词: devourer 过去式: devoured 过去分词: devoured 现在分词: devouring 第三人称单数: devours');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sin', '[sɪn]', 'n.原罪 v.犯罪；违反(教规)', '1. He thinks it\'s a sin to covet other\'s properties. 他认为贪图他人的财物是有罪的。 2. I guess ignorance must be a sin. 我认为无知是一种罪。 3. We\'ve sinned against you, and against our fellow men. 我们得罪了你，也得罪了我们的邻人。 4. We are ashamed of sin and yet not ashamed to sin. 我们耻于罪而不耻于犯罪。', '过去式: sinned 过去分词: sinned 现在分词: sinning 第三人称单数: sins 形容词: sinful');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('instruction', '[ɪn\'strʌkʃn]', 'n.指令；教学；教诲；说明', '1. The robot follows the instructions given by the computer. 机器人听从计算机给出的指令。 2. Under no circumstances should we neglect the quality of instruction at vocational secondary schools. 任何时候都不要忽略职业中学的教学质量问题。 3. We can derive pleasure, experience, and instruction from good books. 好书能给我们乐趣,经验和教诲。 4. I will take the medicine according to the instructions. 我会按说明来服药的。', '形容词: instructional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vegetarian', '[ˌvedʒə\'teriən]', 'n.素食者 adj.素食的', '1. Pulses are a good source of protein for vegetarians. 对于素食者来说,豆类食物是蛋白质的理想来源。 2. He became a vegetarian right then and there. 从那时起，他成了一个素食者。 3. I find it very amazing that she is a vegetarian. 我发现非常惊人的是她是个素食者。 4. A vegetarian gets protein not from meat but from its analogues. 素食者所摄取的蛋白质不是来自肉类而是来自近似肉类的食物。 5. Not a few of my friends are vegetarian. 我朋友中不少人吃素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('twinkling', '[\'twɪŋklɪŋ]', 'adj.闪烁的 动词twinkle的现在分词形式.', '1. He disappeared in a twinkling of an eye. 转眼间他就无影无踪了。 2. Above were the twinkling stars in the night sky. 头顶上就是夜空中闪闪的星星。 3. He stared up at the stars twinkling in the sky above him. 他抬眼凝视着头顶上方星光闪烁的天空。 4. She smiled at me with her unforgettable twinkling blue eyes. 她冲我微微一笑，那双迷人的蓝眼睛叫人难忘。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jerk', '[dʒɜːrk]', 'v.急动；猛拉 n.猛拉；急动；笨蛋；<俚> 蠢人 adj.颠簸不稳的', '1. The bus jerked to a stop. 公共汽车猛然刹车停住了。 2. He jerked the string and the puppet jumped. 他猛地一拉绳子，木偶就跳了起来。 3. He give his tooth a sharp jerk and it come out 他猛一使劲把牙拔了下来 4. The knife was stuck but she pulled it out with a jerk. 那把刀子被卡住了，她猛地一拔，把它拔了出来。', '副词: jerkingly 名词: jerker 过去式: jerked 过去分词: jerked 现在分词: jerking 第三人称单数: jerks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('patch', '[pætʃ]', 'n.小片；补丁；眼罩；（贴在伤口的）膏药；【生态】斑块 vt.修补；补缀；解决；掩饰', '1. The ground is wet in patches. 地上湿处片片。 2. He reset a patch of land with tomato plants. 他在一小块地上重新种上番茄。 3. She sewed a patch onto the knee of the trousers. 她在裤子的膝部打了个补丁. 4. He would indeed seek to patch things up. 他一定会设法把事情加以补救。', '形容词: patchable 名词: patcher 过去式: patched 过去分词: patched 现在分词: patching 第三人称单数: patches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equivocal', '[ɪ\'kwɪvəkl]', 'adj.模棱两可的；意义不明确的', '1. The politician gave an equivocal answer. 那政客的答复模棱两可。 2. The ancient oracles were often vague and equivocal. 古代的神谕常是意义模糊和模棱两可的。 3. The experiments produced equivocal results. 这些实验产生的结果难以理解。 4. The archaeological evidence for ancient cookery is equivocal. 考古学关于古代烹饪的证据是意义不明的。', '副词: equivocally 名词: equivocality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ancient', '[\'eɪnʃənt]', 'adj.古老的；古代的 n.古人', '1. This is an ancient parable. 这是一个古老的寓言。 2. It\'s an ancient tale which appears in various guises in several languages. 那是一个以几种语言叙述的古老的故事。 3. Soldiers in ancient time used escutcheon to fight. 古代的士兵用饰有花纹的盾作战。 4. This stone axe is a relic of ancient times. 这把石斧是古代的遗物。 5. The ancients believed that the sun and moon were planets. 古人相信太阳和月亮都是星球。', '副词: anciently 名词: ancientness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('authoritative', '[ə\'θɔːrəteɪtɪv]', 'adj.权威性的；命令式的', '1. This is an authoritative biography. 这是一本具有权威性的传记。 2. They have not yet relinquished the childish need for an authoritative father. 他们还没有消除儿童对一个权威性的父亲的需要。 3. I make no claims that either are authoritative or independent. 我没有提出任何命令式的或者独立的权利主张。', '副词: authoritatively 名词: authoritativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rite', '[raɪt]', 'n.仪式；典礼', '1. The rite is more than a transition into adulthood. 这个仪式不仅仅象征着变成成年人。 2. There is a rite, for example, among my hunters. 比如说，我的那些猎人就有一种仪式。 3. The mock spanking administered to a birthday boy or girl recalls a rite that has long been an integral feature of many initiation ceremonies. 孩子过生日时，假装打他们的屁股使人们回想起一种仪式，这种仪式是很多成人典礼中不可缺少的一个步骤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('smell', '[smel]', 'n.气味；嗅觉；嗅 v.嗅；闻；散发气味；有臭味；察觉', '1. The strong smell made me throw up. 这强烈的气味使我呕吐了。 2. The cheese was emitting a strong smell. 干酪散发出强烈的气味。 3. Dogs have a keen sense of smell. 狗的嗅觉很灵敏。 4. Hydrogen has no colour, no taste and no smell. 氢气无色、无味、无嗅。 5. Specially-trained dogs can smell out drugs. 受过特殊训练的狗能嗅出毒品。', '过去式: smelled/smelt 过去分词: smelled/smelt 现在分词: smelling 第三人称单数: smells');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('occur', '[ə\'kɜːr]', 'vi.发生；存在；出现；想到', '1. That plane crash occurred only minutes after take-off. 空难在起飞几分钟后就发生了。 2. Misprints occur on every page. 每页都有印刷错误。 3. A connection error might occur. 可能会出现连接错误。 4. Didn\'t it occur to you that he was lying? 你当时没想到他在撒谎吗？', '过去式: occurred 过去分词: occurred 现在分词: occurring 第三人称单数: occurs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('achieve', '[ə\'tʃiːv]', 'v.完成；达到；实现', '1. I\'ve achieved only half of what I\'d hoped to do. 我希望做到的,我仅完成了一半。 2. Work hard, and you will achieve your goal. 好好干,你就会达到自己的目标。 3. You will achieve your ambition if you work hard. 如果你努力, 你的抱负是可以实现的。', '形容词: achievable 名词: achiever 过去式: achieved 过去分词: achieved 现在分词: achieving 第三人称单数: achieves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yelp', '[jelp]', 'n.吠；叫喊声 v.吠；叫喊', '1. The dog gave a yelp when I trod on its paw. 我踩了那狗的爪子，它嚎叫了一声。 2. She let out a yelp of pain. 她痛得叫了一声。 3. She jumped back with a little yelp of surprise. 她吃惊地喊叫了一声跳了回去。 4. The dog yelped and ran away. 狗汪汪叫着跑开了。', '名词: yelper 过去式: yelped 过去分词: yelped 现在分词: yelping 第三人称单数: yelps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acquaint', '[ə\'kweɪnt]', 'vt.使了解；使熟知；告知', '1. We should first try to acquaint ourselves with the facts. 我们先要想法了解事实。 2. These books acquaint Chinese readers with the ancient cultures of these lands. 这些书帮助中国读者了解这些地区的古代文化。 3. You must acquaint yourself with your new duties. 你必须熟悉自己的新职务。 4. Please acquaint him with my arrival. 请通知他我到了。', '过去式: acquainted 过去分词: acquainted 现在分词: acquainting 第三人称单数: acquaints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('divide', '[dɪ\'vaɪd]', 'vt.划分；隔开；分割；[数]除 vi.分裂；分开 n.分水岭；分歧；分', '1. White lines divide the playing area into sections. 这些白线把赛区分成各个部分。 2. I hope this disagreement will not divide us. 我希望我们不会因这分歧而对立起来。 3. Divide the cake into equal parts. 把蛋糕分成等份。 4. Six divided by two is three. 六除以二得三。 5. Class differences can divide a nation. 阶级差异会造成国家的分裂。 6. This led to a divide between the upper class and the common man that persists to a degree down to the present generation. 这导致上层社会和平民大众之间的隔阂，在某种程度上，这个隔阂持续到当代。', '形容词: dividable 过去式: divided 过去分词: divided 现在分词: dividing 第三人称单数: divides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proclaim', '[prə\'kleɪm]', 'vt.正式宣布；声明；表明；赞扬', '1. The president proclaimed that a new currency would be issued. 总统宣布将发行新货币。 2. She did not proclaim her intention. 她没有把自己的意图明说出来。 3. He was impelled to proclaim his doctrine. 他不得不宣扬他的教义。 4. His accent proclaimed that he was an American. 他的口音表明他是一个美国人。', '形容词: proclamatory 名词: proclaimer 过去式: proclaimed 过去分词: proclaimed 现在分词: proclaiming 第三人称单数: proclaims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exposure', '[ɪk\'spoʊʒər]', 'n.暴露；揭露；胶片；曝光时间；(在电视、报纸等媒体上的)亮相；挨冻', '1. Exposure of the body to strong sunlight can be harmful. 身体受烈日暴晒会造成伤害。 2. Her skin was dry after exposure to the wind. 经过风吹后她的皮肤很干。 3. His election toppled down due to the exposure of his bribery. 他的竞选因为受贿被揭露而失败了。 4. How many exposures have you left? 还剩多少底片没有照？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prolong', '[prə\'lɔːŋ]', 'vt.延长；拖延', '1. How can we endeavor to prolong the brevity of human life? 我们怎样才能延长短促的人生？ 2. The meeting may be prolonged into the evening because so many problems have to be solved tonight. 会议可能要延长到夜里，因为今晚有太多问题要解决。 3. Low leakage current helps to prolong battery life. 低漏电流有助于延长电池使用寿命。 4. Clear evidence of his intent is to prolong the ritual. 显然他意在拖延典礼时间。', '名词: prolonger 过去式: prolonged 过去分词: prolonged 现在分词: prolonging 第三人称单数: prolongs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('designate', '[\'dezɪɡneɪt]', 'vt.指定；标明；把...定名为；选派 adj.指定的', '1. She was designated sportswoman of the year. 她被指定为本年度的体坛明星。 2. The chairman has designated that boy as his successor. 主席已经指定那个男孩作他的继承人。 3. Black lines designate boundaries on this map. 在这幅地图上黑线标示疆界。 4. The ruler of a kingdom is designated a king. 王国的统治者称作国王。 5. The ambassador designate is going to meet honored foreign guests. 大使指定人选将要迎接外国贵客。', '形容词: designative 名词: designator 过去式: designated 过去分词: designated 现在分词: designating 第三人称单数: designates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prelude', '[\'preljuːd]', 'n. 序幕； 前奏； 预兆 vi. 成为 ... 的前奏（开头）', '1. It opened the prelude to Chinese civilization. 这掀开了中华文明的序幕。 2. The rural reform has opened the prelude of China\'s reform and opening-up. 农村改革揭开了中国改革开放的序幕。 3. That is the prelude to a ruined evening. 那一晚的约会就在这前奏声中毁了。 4. An intercultural dialogue should prelude such cooperative undertakings. 文化间的对话应该成为这些合作的前奏。 5. The discussions were a prelude to the treaty. 这些讨论是签订该条约的前奏。', '形容词: preludial 名词: preluder 过去式: preluded 过去分词: preluded 现在分词: preluding 第三人称单数: preludes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insanity', '[ɪn\'sænəti]', 'n.疯狂；精神错乱；荒唐', '1. Genius is but one remove from insanity. 天才与疯狂之间只有毫厘之差。 2. Love: a temporary insanity curable by marriage. 爱情：可以由婚姻治愈的暂时的疯狂。 3. Love is a temporary insanity curable by marriage. 爱情是暂时性的癫狂,必须用婚姻来治愈。 4. In his defense he alleged temporary insanity. 在答辩中，他提出短暂的精神错乱为借口。', '名词复数: insanities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('compel', '[kəm\'pel]', 'v.强迫；迫使；使不得已', '1. Nothing can compel me to do such a thing. 没有什么可以强迫我做这件事。 2. I was compelled to do so by absolute necessity. 我因绝对的需要,被迫这样做的。 3. The heavy rain compelled us to stay indoors. 大雨迫使我们呆在户内。 4. Duty compelled the soldiers to volunteer for the mission. 责任驱使军人必须志愿加入此任务', '形容词: compellable 副词: compellably 名词: compeller 过去式: compelled 过去分词: compelled 现在分词: compelling 第三人称单数: compels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gradual', '[\'ɡrædʒuəl]', 'adj.逐渐的；逐步的；平缓的', '1. This leads to gradual memory exhaustion. 这将导致存储空间逐渐的耗尽。 2. There has been a gradual increase in the number of people owning cars. 拥有汽车的人数一直在逐渐上升。 3. I advocate a policy of gradual reform. 我拥护逐步改革的政策。 4. Gradual change is preferable to sudden, large- scale change. 逐步的变化比突然的、大规模的变化更好。', '副词: gradually 名词: gradualness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('predecessor', '[\'predəsesər]', 'n.祖先；前任；原有事物', '1. The Yunxian Man fossil skull is believed by scientists to belong to homo erectus, a predecessor of homo sapiens that walked on their two legs with an upright body posture. 科学家们认为袁县人属于直立人，是靠两条腿直立行走的智力人的祖先。 2. Recently unearthed fossils trace whales to a doglike predecessor of hoofed plant-eaters, and genetic analysis has identified hippos as whales\' closest living relatives. 最近出土的化石使鲸的祖先可追溯到一种有蹄外形像狗的植食动物，而且基因分析证实了现存动物中河马是鲸的近亲。 3. He undid most of the good work of his predecessor. 他把前任的大部分业绩毁掉了。 4. Our new doctor is much younger than his predecessor. 我们新来的医生比他的前任年轻许多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relieve', '[rɪ\'liːv]', 'v.救济；减轻；解除；偷', '1. The Government acted quickly to relieve the widespread distress caused by the earthquake. 地震造成大范围的灾难,政府迅速采取行动赈济灾民。 2. This medicine will relieve your headache. 这药将减轻你的头痛。 3. The route was designed to relieve traffic congestion. 这条路是为缓解交通拥挤而开辟的。 4. The general was relieved of his command. 将军被解除了指挥权。', '形容词: relievable 名词: reliever 过去式: relieved 过去分词: relieved 现在分词: relieving 第三人称单数: relieves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feign', '[feɪn]', 'vt.假装；捏造 vi.假装；装作', '1. People may feign incapability to fraudulently claim the benefits, thus depriving the really needy. 人可能假装无能欺诈索赔的好处，从而剥夺了真正有需要的。 2. People may feign incapability to fraudulently claim the benefits, thus depriving the really needy. 人可能假装无能欺诈索赔的好处，从而剥夺了真正有需要的。 3. To feign frankness is a ruse of war. 装作坦白，是为了作战的目的。', '过去式: feigned 过去分词: feigned 现在分词: feigning 第三人称单数: feigns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chart', '[tʃɑːrt]', 'n.图表；规划图；排行榜 v.制成图表；绘制地图；规划', '1. Can you read the weather chart? 你能看懂气象图吗？ 2. They laid out the chart of their destiny to come. 他们展开了他们未来命运的蓝图。 3. Joyride topped the US chart in spring 1991. 专辑《逍遥游》于1991年春荣登美国排行榜榜首。 4. On the map we chart the course of the river. 我们在地图上标出了该河的流向。', '过去式: charted 过去分词: charted 现在分词: charting 第三人称单数: charts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('connivance', '[kə\'naɪvəns]', 'n.默许；纵容；共谋 =connivence.', '1. The criminals could not have escaped without your connivance. 囚犯没有你的默契配合，是逃不掉的。 2. He was accused of connivance in the riot. 他被指控在暴动上的纵容。 3. The crime was committed with the connivance of a police officer. 这项罪行是在警察的纵容下发生的。 4. He tried to bribe the police into connivance. 他企图收买警察放他一马。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exquisite', '[ɪk\'skwɪzɪt]', 'adj.精挑细选的；精致的；细腻的；强烈的 n.过分在意外表着装的人', '1. The hostess had exquisite taste in clothes. 女主人对衣著十分讲究。 2. The girl came up with a set of exquisite stamps. 那姑娘拿出一套精美的邮票。 3. Her skirt has very exquisite lace. 她的裙子有非常精致的花边。 4. The bracelet was made with exquisite workmanship. 这只手镯做得巧夺天工。', '副词: exquisitely 名词: exquisiteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swift', '[swɪft]', 'adj.快的；迅速的；敏捷的 n.雨燕；线轴 Swift. n.斯威夫特（人名）', '1. His landing is both swift and sure. 他的落地既快又稳。 2. He made a remarkably swift recovery. 他康复得相当快。 3. They\'ve been very swift to deny these rumors. 他们在辟谣方面反应迅速。 4. With the failure of the peace talks, all hopes of a swift end to the war have flown out of the window. 和谈失败后,迅速结束战争的希望都已化为乌有。 5. feel a strong antagonism for sb 6. The Augustan age of English literature includes the writers Dryden, Swift and Pope. 在英国文学的全盛时期 有德莱顿，斯威夫特和蒲柏等文豪。', '副词: swiftly 比较级: swifter 最高级: swiftest 名词: swiftness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sieve', '[sɪv]', 'n.筛子；粗篮；说话轻率不能保密的人 v.筛；滤', '1. We can separate the stones out with a sieve. 我们可以用一个筛子把石头分离出来。 2. This boat leaks like a sieve,ie very badly. 这条船漏得像个筛子。 3. We often shake flour through a sieve. 我们经常用筛子筛面粉。 4. You\'ll need to sieve out the stone from the soil. 你得将石块从土中筛出。', '过去式: sieved 过去分词: sieved 现在分词: sieving 第三人称单数: sieves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('uprising', '[\'ʌpraɪzɪŋ]', 'n.起义；升起 动词uprise的现在分词.', '1. The uprising is just like a mighty storm. 起义犹如暴风骤雨。 2. The Nanchang Uprising marked a new stage for the revolution. 南昌起义标志着革命进人了新阶段。 3. The reactionary regime was thrown down by an armed uprising . 那个反动政权被一次武装起义推翻了。 4. One was a lifelike dragon and the other an uprising phoenix. 一个是栩栩如生的龙，一个是飘飘欲飞的凤。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quantitative', '[\'kwɑːntəteɪtɪv]', 'adj.数量的；定量的', '1. He said it was only a quantitative difference. 他说这仅仅是数量上的差别。 2. Arms races have a quantitative and a qualitative aspects. 军备竞赛具有数量和质量两个方面。 3. We need to do a proper quantitative analysis of this problem. 我们需要对这个问题进行适当的定量分析。 4. The primary research method will be both qualitative and quantitative. 本文采用定性和定量相结合的研究方法。', '副词: quantitatively 名词: quantitativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appropriate', '[ə\'proʊpriət]', 'adj.适当的；相称的 vt.占用；拨出(款项)', '1. You will be informed of the details at the appropriate time. 在适当的时候将把详情告诉你。 2. It is not easy to choose clothes which are appropriate to your beautiful figure. 选择与你漂亮的体型相称的服装是不容易的。 3. She again entreated his forgiveness for so selfishly appropriating the cottage 她为自己这么自私地占用了这座农舍而再次恳求他的原谅。 4. The government has appropriated some funds for education. 政府拨出了一些款项用作教育基金。', '形容词: appropriative 副词: appropriately 名词: appropriateness 过去式: appropriated 过去分词: appropriated 现在分词: appropriating 第三人称单数: appropriates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('politics', '[\'pɑːlətɪks]', 'n.政治；政治学；政治活动；政治策略；政见', '1. This letter does not pertain to politics. 这封信的内容与政治无关。 2. He is not interested in politics. 他不喜欢政治。 3. In politics Britain has preferred evolution to revolution. 在政治上，英国喜欢渐进而不喜欢革命。 4. He has serious aspirations to a career in politics. 他有从政的雄心壮志。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('channel', '[\'tʃænl]', 'n.频道；海峡；方法；通道；（消息）渠道 vt.引导；形成河道；集中（精力）', '1. This channel comes on the air every morning at 7 am. 这个频道每天早晨7点钟开始播放。 2. The ship went through the English Channel fast. 那条船很快的通过了英吉利海峡。 3. She was seeking a channel for her creative energies. 她正在为她创造性的能量寻找方法。 4. We can reach these markets through our existing distribution channels. 我们可以通过我们现有的分散渠道到达这些市场。 5. All information on the classes is channeled through the principal\'s office. 课上的所有信息都被传到校长办公室了', '名词: channeler 过去式: channeled/channelled 过去分词: channeled/channelled 现在分词: channeling/channelling 第三人称单数: channels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('battery', '[\'bætəri]', 'n.电池；一系列；炮兵连；排炮；[律]殴打', '1. They are electrifying the battery. 他们正给电池充电。 2. My car battery has run down; it needs recharging. 我的汽车电池没电了，需要充电。 3. We would undergo a battery of tests. 我们要进行一系列试验。 4. A captain commands a company or battery. 一个上尉指挥一个连队或炮兵连。', '名词复数: batteries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('check', '[tʃɛk]', 'v.检查；阻止；核对；买单 n.检查；阻碍；支票；账单；方格图案；(国际象棋)将军', '1. Do look out for spelling mistakes when you check your homework. 你检查作业时要当心拼写错误。 2. We had to check this tendency for administrative reasons. 由于市政管理的原因，我们不得不阻止这种趋势。 3. Please check the date. 请核实一下日期。 4. We conduct regular check on the quality of our products. 我们对产品做例行质量检查。', '形容词: checkable 过去式: checked 过去分词: checked 现在分词: checking 第三人称单数: checks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reveal', '[rɪ\'viːl]', 'vt.显示；透露；揭示；展现 n.(外墙与门或窗之间的)窗侧；门侧；(汽车的)窗框', '1. Several withered trees on the sides of the road reveal the desolation here. 道路两旁的几棵枯木显示出这里的荒凉。 2. His deed revealed him to be a kind man. 他的行为显示他是个好心的人。 3. The journalist did not want to reveal the identity of his informant. 那个新闻工作者不想透露消息提供人的身分。 4. He would not reveal what decisions had been reached. 他不肯透露做出了什么决定。', '形容词: revealable 名词: revealer 过去式: revealed 过去分词: revealed 现在分词: revealing 第三人称单数: reveals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acid', '[\'æsɪd]', 'n.酸；酸性物质；<俚>迷幻药 adj.酸的；酸性的；尖酸的', '1. Acids react with bases to form salts. 酸与碱反应生成盐。 2. The acid burnt a hole in the carpet. 酸把地毯烧了个洞。 3. The acid has burnt a hole in my jacket. 这种酸把我的上衣烧了一个窟窿。 4. The acid in the rain slowly ate away at the stone wall. 雨水中的酸性物质慢慢侵蚀着石墙。 5. Add more sugar if it tastes too acid. 如果尝着太酸的话就多放点糖。', '副词: acidly 名词: acidness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tally', '[\'tæli]', 'n.帐；记分；一致；标签 vt.计算；记录；使一致 vi.计算；记分；一致', '1. Don\'t forget to keep a careful tally of what you spend. 别忘了仔细记下你的开支帐目。 2. You can buy on tally in this shop. 在这家商店里可以赊购。 3. He added to his tally in the last minute. 他在比赛最后一分钟又得了分。 4. All the figures tally with the projected total. 合计和预算的总额一致。 5. The tally of computation and observation is in a good agreement. 将计算值与实测资料比较，结果表明符合程度良好。 6. The tally of computation and observation is in a good agreement. 将计算值与实测资料比较，结果表明符合程度良好。', '名词复数: tallies 过去式: tallied 过去分词: tallied 现在分词: tallying 第三人称单数: tallies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('climax', '[\'klaɪmæks]', 'n.高潮；极点；层进法；[生]顶极群落；巅峰，最高峰', '1. The music approached a climax. 乐曲接近高潮。 2. The climax of the celebration was a firework display. 庆祝会的高潮是燃放烟火。 3. The heat of summer has reached its climax. 已经是夏季最热的天气了。 4. The air war over Europe was reaching its climax. 欧洲的空战已近白热化。', '过去式: climaxed 过去分词: climaxed 现在分词: climaxing 第三人称单数: climaxes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dangle', '[\'dæŋɡl]', 'v.摇晃；悬垂；挂着；追求 n.摇摆；摇摆物', '1. The leaves dangled in the wind. 树叶随风摇摆。 2. He dangled the bone in front of the puppy. 他晃动着骨头逗小狗。 3. The children sat on the high wall, with their legs dangling. 小孩子们坐在高墙上，脚悬垂着。 4. Huge earrings dangled from her ears. 她的耳朵上吊着巨大的耳环。 5. Do not swing it backwards or let it dangle. 不要将腿向后摇摆或者悬吊空中。', '形容词: dangly 名词: dangler 过去式: dangled 过去分词: dangled 现在分词: dangling 第三人称单数: dangles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('envelop', '[ɪn\'veləp]', 'vt.包封；遮盖；包围', '1. The papers are enveloped by plastic bag. 论文用塑料纸包封好了。 2. Gloom enveloped the household. 沮丧的气氛笼罩著这一家子。 3. The mountain peak was enveloped in mist and clouds. 山峰被云雾遮蔽。 4. The building was soon enveloped in flames. 那幢建筑物很快就陷入了火海之中。', '名词: enveloper 过去式: enveloped 过去分词: enveloped 现在分词: enveloping 第三人称单数: envelops');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('granite', '[\'ɡrænɪt]', 'n.花岗石', '1. The valley ended in a perpendicular rim of granite. 那山谷的尽头是花岗石的断崖。 2. He has a heart of granite. 他有一副铁石心肠。 3. He is pointing down a block of granite. 他正在用锐利的工具修整一块花岗石。 4. The old man\'s grave is made of granite. 那老人的墓是用花岗石造的。', '形容词: granitic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('backward', '[\'bækwərd]', 'adj.向后的；落后的 adv.向后', '1. He took a backward step and ran away. 他向后退了一步,跑了。 2. This part of the country is still backward. 这个国家的这个地区仍很落后。 3. Although he is clever, he is backward in giving his views. 他虽然很聪明，却不善发表他的意见。 4. He looked backward over his shoulder. 他回头向后看。', '副词: backwardly 名词: backwardness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('turnpike', '[\'tɜːrnpaɪk]', 'n.收费公路', '1. You have to pay a toll to drive on a turnpike. 在收费公路上开车要缴通行税。 2. A lot of motels lie beside the turnpike. 很多汽车旅馆都位于付费公路旁边。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crevice', '[\'krevɪs]', 'n.(岩石、墙等)裂缝', '1. Some grass grow in the crevice of the stone wall. 有些草从石墙的裂缝中长出来。 2. The earth heaved and surged, and instantly a large crevice split open. 地面一阵晃动，瞬即裂开一条大缝。', '形容词: creviced');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stunt', '[stʌnt]', 'n.特技；阻碍成长 vt.阻碍成长；表演特技', '1. Have you watched a stunt flying? 你看过特技飞行表演吗? 2. The stunt pilot looped his plane. 特技飞行员驾机在天上转圆圈。 3. Her latest stunt is riding a motor cycle through a ring of flames. 她的最新特技表演是骑摩托车钻火圈。 4. Lack of the right food may stunt growth. 缺乏适当的食物会阻碍发育。', '名词: stuntedness 过去式: stunted 过去分词: stunted 现在分词: stunting 第三人称单数: stunts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recoil', '[rɪ\'kɔɪl]', 'v.退却；畏缩；弹回；报应 n.畏缩；弹回；后坐力', '1. She recoiled at the sight of the snake. 她一见到蛇就往后缩。 2. You have to learn not to recoil from touching the insects. 你必须学会碰到昆虫而不退缩。 3. A gun recoils after being fired. 枪在射击后向后坐。 4. Plots sometimes recoil on the plotters. 阴谋有时会报应在阴谋者身上。 5. The pain of it made him recoil from the exuberance of holiday shoppers. 这痛苦使他在节日里兴高采烈的顾客面前显得有些畏缩。', '名词: recoiler 过去式: recoiled 过去分词: recoiled 现在分词: recoiling 第三人称单数: recoils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('parallel', '[\'pærəlel]', 'adj.平行的；相同的；类似的；并联的 n.对比；平行线(面)；双杠；相似物 vt.相比；相应；与 ... 平行', '1. In the parallel world, there might be an answer for everything. 在平行世界里,似乎有一切的答案。 2. Parallel processing is the most important peculiarity in this design. 其中,并行化的设计理念是该设计的最大特点。 3. The railway lines run parallel to the road. 铁路线和那条道路平行。 4. My experience in this matter is parallel to yours. 在这件事情上，我的经验和你的类似。 5. It is inappropriate to draw such a parallel. 这种比拟是不恰当的。 6. No one can parallel him in Math. 在数学方面无人能与他匹敌。', '过去式: paralleled/parallelled 过去分词: paralleled/parallelled 现在分词: paralleling/parallelling 第三人称单数: parallels/parallels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abort', '[ə\'bɔːrt]', 'v.流产；堕胎；中止', '1. The virus can cause pregnant animals to abort. 这种病毒可能导致怀孕动物流产。 2. The doctor had to abort the baby. 医生只好将胎儿引产。 3. The captain instructed them to abort the mission. 上尉指示他们中止执行任务。', '过去式: aborted 过去分词: aborted 现在分词: aborting 第三人称单数: aborts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enroll', '[ɪn\'roʊl]', 'v.登记；招收；入伍', '1. He enrolled our names. 他把我们的名字登记下来了。 2. He enrolled with an employment agency for a secretary. 他在职业介绍所登记要当秘书。 3. This school plan to enroll 100 students every year. 该校每年只招收100名学生。 4. His son was enrolled for military service a couple of years ago. 他儿子在两三年前应募入伍。', '名词: enrollee');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('peripheral', '[pə\'rɪfərəl]', 'adj.外围的；不重要的 n.外围设备', '1. We dealt with the peripheral aspects of a cost reduction program. 我们谈到了降低成本计划的一些外围问题。 2. The talks made progress on peripheral issues, but failed to resolve the main dispute between the two sides. 谈判在次要的问题上取得了进展,但是没能解决双方的主要争端。 3. Unfortunately, the speeds of peripheral devices have not kept pace. 不幸的是外围设备的速度跟不上主机。 4. It minimizes distortion and peripheral vignetting at the wide end. 资讯科技将扭曲和在广泛的结束使晕映的外围设备减到最少。', '副词: peripherally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bequest', '[bɪ\'kwest]', 'n.遗产；遗赠物', '1. He left a bequest to each of his grandchildren. 他给他的孙子孙女每人留下一笔遗产。 2. We must note to protect our national bequest. 我们必须注意保护自己的民族遗产。 3. The picture was acquired by bequest in 1921. 这幅画是在1921年通过遗赠获得的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spleen', '[spliːn]', 'n.脾；脾气；怒气', '1. The spleen is the source of phlegm production. 脾为生痰之源。 2. The stomach lies between the liver and the spleen. 胃位于肝和脾之间。 3. I waited for him to get the rest of the spleen out of his system. 我等着他把心头的余努全部发泄出来。 4. When I get frustrated and angry, I have to vent my spleen on someone. 我受尽挫折，怒火冲天时，禁不住想找谁发一顿脾气。', '形容词: spleeny');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ascribe', '[ə\'skraɪb]', 'v.归因于；归于', '1. He ascribes his success to good luck. 他把他的成功归功于幸运。 2. You should not ascribe your failure to bad luck. 你不应该把自己的失败归因于运气不好。 3. It \'s wrong to ascribe all that have happened simply to the war . 把发生的一切归咎于战争是错误的。 4. This song is often ascribed to Bach. 这首歌曲常被说成是巴赫做的。', '过去式: ascribed 过去分词: ascribed 现在分词: ascribing 第三人称单数: ascribes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tangle', '[\'tæŋɡl]', 'n.缠结；混乱；纠纷 vt.使缠结；使混乱；使陷入 vi.纠缠；乱作一团；<口>吵架；争论', '1. The wool got in a fearful tangle. 毛线乱成了一团。 2. His financial affairs are in such a tangle. 他的钱财是糊涂帐。 3. We employed a lawyer to straighten our legal tangle. 我们雇了一位律师把法律纠纷理出头绪。 4. The little girl tangled the yarn her mother was knitting. 小女孩把她妈妈在编结的毛线弄得纠结在一起了。 5. He was really a tough guy to tangle with. 他真是一个难缠的人。', '形容词: tangly 过去式: tangled 过去分词: tangled 现在分词: tangling 第三人称单数: tangles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incite', '[ɪn\'saɪt]', 'v.煽动；刺激；激励', '1. Stop anyone trying to incite the people. 有人煽动，实行挡驾。 2. On Sabertron, the Destrons incite an uprising among the prisoners. 塞伯特恩之迪斯坦逆党煽动囚犯暴动。', '名词: incitement 过去式: incited 过去分词: incited 现在分词: inciting 第三人称单数: incites');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abreast', '[ə\'brest]', 'adv.并肩地；跟上', '1. The four of them walked abreast. 四人并肩而行。 2. They walked two or three abreast. 他们两三个人一排地走着。 3. Hayes\' horse fell abreast of his father\'s. 海斯和他父亲骑马并肩而行。 4. Many people stood abreast to listen to him. 许多人并肩站着听他说话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inactivate', '[ɪn\'æktɪveɪt]', 'v.使不活跃；〈化〉破坏...的活性', '1. ACT Activate specified window. /INA Inactivate specified window. ACT激活指定的窗口.;/INA取消指定窗口的激活状态 2. Inactivate the selected network device so that it cannot be used. 停用所选的网络设备。 3. They quickly inactivate vegetative forms, but their sporicidal action is slow. 它能迅速灭活繁殖体，但其杀孢子能力低。 4. GI microflora may inactivate certain drugs, reducing their absorption. 胃肠道内的菌丛可使某些药物失活，降低药物的吸收。', '名词: inactivation 过去式: inactivated 过去分词: inactivated 现在分词: inactivating 第三人称单数: inactivates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pursuit', '[pər\'suːt]', 'n.追求；追赶；工作', '1. His life is spent in the pursuit of pleasure. 他一生都在寻欢作乐。 2. We work hard in pursuit of happy life. 我们为追求幸福生活而努力工作。 3. What\'s your favorite pursuit? 你的爱好是什么？ 4. He exercises everyday in pursuit of health. 他为了健康而每天锻炼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dye', '[daɪ]', 'n.染料；染色 v.染；染色', '1. The dye works its way in. 染料渗透进去了。 2. A good dye will not fade. 染得好的颜色不会褪色。 3. The dye doesn\'t take in cold water. 那种染料在冷水中不起作用。 4. After mercerizing, the goods are sent to the dye house or colour shop. 绦光后的产品送往染色车间或印花车间。 5. They used only natural pigments to dye the wool. 他们只用天然颜料染毛织品。', '名词: dyer 过去式: dyed 过去分词: dyed 现在分词: dyeing 第三人称单数: dyes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('applicant', '[\'æplɪkənt]', 'n.申请人', '1. He gave every new applicant the once-over. 他匆匆地看一下每一个新来的申请人。 2. As the wage of the job was low, there were few applicants for it. 因为工资低,没有什么人申请这份工作。 3. The enterprise is an applicant of this credit. 这家企业是信用证的申请者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('innate', '[ɪ\'neɪt]', 'adj.天生的；固有的', '1. Ability is not innate, but comes through practice. 本事不是天生的，是锻炼出来的。 2. You obviously have an innate talent for music. 你显然有天生的音乐才能。 3. Children have an innate ability to learn language. 孩子具有天生的学习语言的能力。 4. The love is the innate strength. 爱是与生俱来的力量!', '副词: innately 名词: innateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incompetent', '[ɪn\'kɑːmpɪtənt]', 'adj.无能力的；不称职的；不能胜任的 n.没有能力的人', '1. The company cleaned out the incompetent workers. 公司把不称职的员工解雇了。 2. One incompetent manager brings along another. 一个不称职的经理人员带进来另一个不胜任的人。 3. One incompetent manager brings along another. 一个不称职的经理人员带进来另一个不胜任的人。 4. His incompetent colleague was axed as a warning to other employees. 作为对其他员工的警告，他的一个不胜任的同事被解聘了。 5. I\'ve had it with these incompetent employees. 我对这些没有能力的员工失去了耐心。', '副词: incompetently 名词: incompetence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exclusion', '[ɪk\'skluːʒn]', 'n.排除；除外；逐出', '1. The exclusion of women from the temple made them feel sad. 妇女被排斥于寺院之外使得她们很难过。 2. Exclusion of air creates a vacuum in the bottle. 瓶子里的空气排除后就产生真空。 3. He spends his spare time gardening, to the exclusion of all other interests. 他把空余时间都用在园艺上了，没有任何其他爱好。 4. His exclusion from the club hurt him very much. 俱乐部赶他出来，他很伤心。', '形容词: exclusionary');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vague', '[veɪɡ]', 'adj.不明确的；模糊的；茫然的；犹豫不决的', '1. At the back of his mind was the vague idea that he had met her before. 他隐隐约约地觉得以前曾经见过她。 2. She is so vague that I can never understand what she is trying to say. 她说话含含糊糊，我怎么也听不明白她想说些什么。 3. His vague ideas crystallized into a definite plan. 他那些模糊的想法变成了一个明确的计划。 4. I\'m quite vague about what happened. 我对发生的事很不了解。', '副词: vaguely 比较级: vaguer 最高级: vaguest 名词: vagueness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acrid', '[\'ækrɪd]', 'adj.苦味的；辛辣的；尖刻的', '1. An acrid brown gum resin is now used mainly in veterinary medicine. 一种苦味棕色的树胶树脂现在主要用于兽用药物。 2. The acrid smell carried across the table. 一股辛辣的味道在桌子周围弥漫开来。 3. This is an acrid and pungent substance. 这是一种辛辣而带刺激性的物质。 4. There is an acrid tone to your remarks. 你说这些话的口气带有讥刺意味。', '副词: acridly 名词: acridity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('naturalist', '[\'nætʃrəlɪst]', 'n.自然主义者；博物学者', '1. He is talking with a naturalist. 他正在和一位自然主义者交谈。 2. The leading naturalist, Emile Zola, enunciated the philosophy of the new school. 法国主要的自然主义者埃米尔·左拉阐明了这种新流派的基本原理。 3. The naturalist told us many stories about birds. 博物学家给我们讲述了许多有关鸟儿的故事。 4. He is a naturalist who studies animals and plants. 他是个研究动植物的博物学家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reptile', '[\'reptaɪl]', 'n.爬行动物；卑鄙的人 adj.爬虫类的', '1. Snakes and crocodiles are reptiles. 蛇和鳄鱼都是爬行动物。 2. Strictly speaking,a slow-worm is a kind of reptile. 严格地说，蛇晰是一种爬行动物。 3. This creature can be subsumed in the class of reptile. 这种生物可以归入爬行动物一类. 4. The land is teeming with reptile life. 这片土地多爬行动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pigment', '[\'pɪɡmənt]', 'n. 色素； 颜料 v. 把 ... 加颜色； 变色', '1. This pigment is a good common food additive. 该色素是稳定性好的食品添加剂。 2. How is retinal pigment denaturation treated? 视网膜色素变性怎样治疗？ 3. The primary white pigment is titanium dioxide. 最重要的白色颜料是二氧化钛。 4. Of course, pigment is not the only part of a fresco. 当然，颜料还不是画面的全部。 5. You just expand or shrink the millions of pigment cells or chromatophores in your skin to instantly change color. 你只需要展开或收缩你皮肤里的上百万个色素细胞或色素体就可以立即变色。', '形容词: pigmentary 过去式: pigmented 过去分词: pigmented 现在分词: pigmenting 第三人称单数: pigments');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fertilizer', '[\'fɜːrtəlaɪzər]', 'n.肥料', '1. The stalks will rot and make good fertilizer. 杆儿腐烂后会成为很好的肥料。 2. Crushed bones make one of the best fertilizers. 碎骨是最好的肥料之一。 3. Farmers bartered rice for fertilizer. 农民们用大米换肥料。 4. The tractor hauled the fertilizer away. 拖拉机把肥料拉走了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immediate', '[ɪ\'miːdiət]', 'adj.直接的；最接近的；立即的；目前的', '1. The immediate cause of death is unknown. 造成死亡的直接原因不明。 2. He seldom expected to receive any immediate profit. 他倒不一定是想从中捞到什么直接的好处。 3. The evidence has no immediate bearing on the case. 该证据与本案无直接关系。 4. His immediate successors fell into the same trap. 他的直接继承者也堕入了这一陷阱。', '名词: immediateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trace', '[treɪs]', 'n.痕迹；微量；踪迹 v.追踪；描绘；找出根源', '1. When the police exhume the corpse they discover trace of poison in it 警方掘出尸体, 发现有中毒的痕迹 2. Traces of blood were found in the bathroom. 在浴室里发现一点血。 3. The police have detected the trace of the murderer after several days of investigation. 警察经过几天的调查,发现了凶手的踪迹。 4. He traces his descent back to an old norman family. 他追踪自己的世系上溯至一个古老的诺曼家族。', '形容词: traceable 副词: traceably 名词: traceability 过去式: traced 过去分词: traced 现在分词: tracing 第三人称单数: traces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beat', '[biːt]', 'v.打；打败；跳动；敲打；战胜 n.拍子；敲打；心跳声 adj.精疲力尽的', '1. His father beat the disobedient boy. 他的父亲打那个不听话的男孩。 2. If we don\'t prepare for the speech contest, they will beat us. 如果这场演讲比赛我们不做好准备的话,他们就会打败我们。 3. He\'s alive；his heart is still beating. 他还活著－－心脏还在跳。 4. They beat drums to cheer up the players. 他们擂鼓给运动员加油。 5. Every member of the band must follow the beat. 乐队的每个成员都必须跟着拍子演奏。 6. I am completely beat. 我累极了。', '过去式: beat 过去分词: beaten/beat 现在分词: beating 第三人称单数: beats');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heed', '[hiːd]', 'v.注意；留心 n.注意；留心', '1. Now heed what I say. 现在注意听我要说的话。 2. She never heeded anyone\'s warning. 她从不理会任何人的警告。 3. Please heed the warning in the banner. 请留心这些警告的标牌。 4. He did not heed my gibes, and chattered on. 他没有留心我的嘲笑,继续喋喋不休地说着。 5. A good leader should always pay heed to the voice of the masses. 一位好领导应该经常注意倾听群众的呼声。', '过去式: heeded 过去分词: heeded 现在分词: heeding 第三人称单数: heeds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('substitute', '[\'sʌbstɪtuːt]', 'n.代用品；代替者；替补队员 vt.代替；用 ... 代替；代以', '1. Water is not a proper substitute for wine. 水不是酒的适当代用品。 2. Is saccharin a good substitute for sugar? 糖精是糖的良好替代品吗? 3. We recommend this brand as a good substitute. 我们推荐的新品种可以完全替代原来的产品。 4. His friend Humboldt was his substitute. 他的朋友洪堡接替了他。 5. Only art can substitute for nature. 唯有艺术能代替自然。', '形容词: substitutable 名词: substitutability 过去式: substituted 过去分词: substituted 现在分词: substituting 第三人称单数: substitutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('permeate', '[\'pɜːrmieɪt]', 'v.弥漫；渗透；普及', '1. His subtle satisfaction seemed to permeate the space around them. 他难以捉摸的满足感好像弥漫在了他们的周围。 2. If your wine is still, pour it into the centre of the glass to let the bouquet permeate the vessel. 如果是无汽泡的酒，直接倒入杯子中央，使酒的香气充分散发，弥漫整个酒杯。 3. Water will permeate blotting paper. 水能渗透吸水纸。 4. Functional relationships permeate every part of science. 函数关系渗透自然科学的每个部分。', '形容词: permeant 名词: permeation 过去式: permeated 过去分词: permeated 现在分词: permeating 第三人称单数: permeates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clutch', '[klʌtʃ]', 'vt.抓住；抓牢 vi.企图抓住；踩离合器 n.抓住；爪子；离合器；紧要关头 n.一窝鸡（蛋）；一群 adj.关键的；致胜的', '1. The boy clutched the marbles and ran away. 那男孩一把抢去弹珠便逃之夭夭。 2. The child clutched his toy. 那个孩子紧抓着他的玩具不放。 3. John jumped up to clutch at the branch,but missed. 约翰跳起来试图抓住那树枝，但是没有成功。 4. It is useless to clutch at a straw. 抓救命稻草是无济于事的。 5. The eagle flew away with a rabbit in the clutch of its claws. 鹰用爪子紧紧抓住一只野兔，飞走了。 6. He\'s won a whole clutch of awards. 他获得一大堆奖。 7. Tmac is a choker and will never be able to get it done during clutch time. 麦迪就像一条围巾，在关键的时候很难从脖子上取下来。', '过去式: clutched 过去分词: clutched 现在分词: clutching 第三人称单数: clutches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scarce', '[skers]', 'adj.缺乏的；不足的；稀少的；罕见的 adv.勉强', '1. Food and fuel were scarce in this region. 这地区食物和燃料都很缺乏。 2. Firewood is scarce in many parts of the world. 世界上很多地区都缺乏木材。 3. Food commands a higher price when it is scarce. 食物(供应)不足时，售价较高。 4. As Singapore is a small island, land is scarce. 新加坡是一个小岛,土地稀有。 5. I could scarce believe my eyes. 我几乎不敢相信自己的眼睛。', '比较级: scarcer 最高级: scarcest 名词: scarceness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repetition', '[ˌrepə\'tɪʃn]', 'n.重复；反复', '1. You should avoid unnecessary repetition. 你应避免不必要的重复。 2. We must avoid the repetition of a mistake. 我们必须避免犯同样的错误。 3. The story loses a great deal in repetition. 这个故事由于反复讲述而大为减色了。 4. The perfomance improved with each repetition. 演出每演一场都有改进。', '形容词: repetitional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('malcontent', '[ˌmælkən\'tent]', 'adj.不服的；不满的 n.不满者；反叛者', '1. But she fears the husband is malcontent to this, even rebuff. 但她担心丈夫对此不满，甚至断然拒绝。 2. We must admit that these statistics reflect many malcontent mood. 必须承认，这些统计数字反映了许多不满情绪。 3. The malcontent is gunning for his supervisor. 那个心怀不满的人在伺机加害他的上司。 4. All the trouble is being caused by a handful of malcontents. 这些是非都是由一小撮不满分子搬弄的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rival', '[\'raɪvl]', 'n.竞争者；对手；同伴 adj.竞争的 v.竞争；与 ... 相匹敌', '1. He is hound out of his job by jealous rival. 他受到忌妒他的竞争者的算计而被迫离职。 2. The party leader has been supplanted by his rival. 那位政党领导已被他的对手取而代之了。 3. He was utterly unscrupulous in his competition with rival firms. 他与对立公司竞争完全不讲道德。 4. Ships can\'t rival aircraft for speed. 轮船在速度方面无法与飞机匹敌。', '过去式: rivaled/rivalled 过去分词: rivaled/rivalled 现在分词: rivaling/rivalling 第三人称单数: rivals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('garb', '[ɡɑːrb]', 'n.打扮；装束；外表 v.打扮；穿衣', '1. A man in the garb of a priest came in. 一个穿着牧师服装的人走了进来。 2. Nod still wore her religious garb since it helped to hide her mercenary nature. 诺德依然保持她的宗教装束，这样可以掩盖其文物贩子的真实身份。 3. No, not at all, I was still in my usual North American overseas Chinese plain garb. 不，完全不是，我还是穿着北美洲华人的朴素装束。 4. Certain political, social, and legal forms reappear in seemingly different garb. 一些政治、社会和法律的形式在表面不同的外衣下重复出现。 5. The woman was garbed in black. 那个女子穿着黑衣。', '过去式: garbed 过去分词: garbed 现在分词: garbing 第三人称单数: garbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genesis', '[\'dʒenəsɪs]', 'n.起源；发生 Genesis：《创世纪》（旧约圣经第一卷）.', '1. Minor change to Genesis support. 对起源的支持略微的改变。 2. We cannot yet satisfactorily explain the genesis of the universe. 我们仍不能令人满意地解释宇宙的起源。 3. These effects are of considerable importance in the genesis of a number of important arrhythmias. 这些效应在某些重要的心律失常的发生上有相当重要的意义。 4. My future work is to use this system to carry out genetic screenings to identify novel genes regulating the neuronal genesis and morphogenesis. 本实验室将利用果蝇进行遗传筛选，寻找影响神经细胞发生及形态形成的分子机制。', '名词复数: geneses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commute', '[kə\'mjuːt]', 'v.通勤；折换；减刑；改变；交换 n.乘车上下班', '1. Mary used to commute five miles from her home in the suburb. 玛丽过去每天从郊区的家里走五英里来上班。 2. They chose to commute equity into license agreements. 他们选择了将股权转换成许可协议。 3. Regular train travellers may commute a single monthly payment for daily tickets. 经常坐火车的人可以按每天的票价折换购买月票。 4. He seemed at times to be asking God to commute these penalties. 有时他好象还恳求上帝减轻惩罚。 5. Her commute to work will be easy. 她上下班交通会很方便。', '过去式: commuted 过去分词: commuted 现在分词: commuting 第三人称单数: commutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('observation', '[ˌɑːbzər\'veɪʃn]', 'n.观察；观察力；注意；评论', '1. The patient was kept under observation all night. 这位病人被观察了一整夜。 2. The law of nature was deduced from observation. 自然法则是从观察中推导出来的。 3. He is a man of little observation. 他是个观察力极差的人。 4. He was endowed with the power of acute observation. 他有敏锐的观察力。', '形容词: observational 副词: observationally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('litter', '[\'lɪtər]', 'n.垃圾；杂乱；一窝(幼仔)；褥草；轿子 v.乱丢垃圾；弄乱；产(幼仔)；用草等给动物铺窝', '1. There was litter strewn all over the pavement. 人行道上到处都是扔的垃圾。 2. The desk was covered with a litter of documents. 书桌上满满地放着一堆杂乱的文件。 3. His litter strewn room really needed to be cleaned. 他杂乱的房间该好好收拾一下了。 4. His dog hasn\'t had a litter of puppies. 他的狗还没有生过一窝小狗。', '名词: litterer 过去式: littered 过去分词: littered 现在分词: littering 第三人称单数: litters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swear', '[swer]', 'v.咒骂；发誓；宣誓 n.誓言；咒骂；发誓', '1. Shut up! How dare you swear at me like that! 住嘴，你竟敢那样咒骂我! 2. You have no right to swear at me like that! 你无权那样咒骂我！ 3. I swear by Almighty God that I will tell the truth. 我对万能的上帝发誓我要说真话。 4. They swore an oath to carry out their duties faithfully. 他们发誓要忠实履行自己的职责。 5. Don\'t forget your swear for me. 不要忘记你对我发过的誓言。', '名词: swearer 过去式: swore 过去分词: sworn 现在分词: swearing 第三人称单数: swears');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accumulate', '[ə\'kjuːmjəleɪt]', 'v.积累；增加；聚集', '1. They set out to accumulate a huge mass of data. 他们开始积累大量的资料。 2. Dust and dirt soon accumulates if a house is not cleaned regularly. 房屋不经常打扫,尘土很快就越积越多。 3. True poetry accumulates meaning every time it is read. 真正好诗愈念涵义愈丰富。 4. However, as the evidence began to accumulate, experts from the zoo felt obliged to investigate. 然而，当证据日趋增多时，该动物园的专家们感到有必要进行调查。', '形容词: accumulable 过去式: accumulated 过去分词: accumulated 现在分词: accumulating 第三人称单数: accumulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forerunner', '[\'fɔːrʌnər]', 'n.先驱；祖先；预兆；[体育]赛前试滑滑道的人', '1. He was the forerunner of the resistance. 他是这个反抗运动的先驱者。 2. She is a forerunner of the modern women\'s movement. 她是现代妇女运动的先驱。 3. Mr. Sun Yat sen is the forerunner of the Chinese revolution. 孙中山先生是中国革命的先驱。 4. Penicillin was the forerunner of modern antibiotics. 青霉素是现代抗生素的先导。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chilly', '[\'tʃɪli]', 'adj.寒冷的；冷淡的 n.干辣椒', '1. It\'s a chilly morning. 这是一个寒冷的早晨。 2. A gust of chilly autumn wind is blowing from the north. 一阵冷飕飕的秋风从北方吹来。 3. It often happens that a balmy morning passes into a chilly afternoon. 一个温和的上午常常转为一个寒冷的下午。 4. The visitors got a very chilly reception. 客人受到了非常冷淡的接待。', '副词: chillily 比较级: chillier 最高级: chilliest 名词: chilliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('influenza', '[ˌɪnflu\'enzə]', 'n.流行性感冒', '1. The girl has come down with influenza. 这女孩得了流行性感冒。 2. She is ill in bed with influenza. 她因患流行性感冒而卧在床上。', '形容词: influenzal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('microwave', '[\'maɪkrəweɪv]', 'n.微波；微波炉 vt.用微波炉加热', '1. The samples were digested using a microwave oven. 用微波消解样品。 2. A land line can be wire or fiber optics or microwave. 陆上线路可以是金属或光纤电缆或者微波线路。 3. We cooked the fish in the microwave oven. 我们在微波炉中煮鱼。 4. It also has a nice dish washer and microwave oven. 一个洗碗机和一个微波炉。 5. Last winter it unveiled a bra that can be heated in a microwave so as to help save on indoor heating costs. 去年冬天，黛安芬公司为了响应日本政府的节能，就推出了一款可以用微波炉加热的文胸，从而减少室内供暖的成本。', '形容词: microwavable 过去式: microwaved 过去分词: microwaved 现在分词: microwaving 第三人称单数: microwaves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('congregate', '[\'kɑːŋɡrɪɡeɪt]', 'v.使集合；聚集；集合 adj.集体的', '1. We are congregated for a meeting. 我们集合起来开会。 2. A crowd quickly congregated round the speaker. 大群的人迅速地在演说者周围聚集起来。 3. The highbrows usually congregate there. 知识界人士通常都在那里聚会。 4. The personal benefit can\'t divide congregate benifit. 个人的利益是与集体的利益分不开的。', '形容词: congregative 名词: congregativeness 过去式: congregated 过去分词: congregated 现在分词: congregating 第三人称单数: congregates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('condition', '[kən\'dɪʃn]', 'n.条件；情况 v.训练；决定；以 ... 为条件；护理（头发）', '1. Conditions in poor quarters were horrible. 城里穷人居住区条件十分糟糕。 2. I had halfway decided to accept their conditions at that time. 当时我已差不多决定要接受他们的条件了。 3. The terrorists will only release their hostage on certain condition. 恐怖分子只有在某些条件下才释放人质。 4. Jimmie had but a vague idea of world conditions now. 杰米对当今世界情况只有一点模糊的了解。 5. I conditioned the dog to bark at strangers. 我训练这只狗对陌生人吠叫。', '过去式: conditioned 过去分词: conditioned 现在分词: conditioning 第三人称单数: conditions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imaginary', '[ɪ\'mædʒɪneri]', 'adj.想象的；虚构的', '1. We play out an imaginary confrontation in our mind. 我们的脑海中浮现出一种想象的冲突。 2. The boy\'s fears were only imaginary. 这小孩的恐惧只是一种想象。 3. People still have a general fear for the imaginary infernal powers. 人们对于虚构的地狱中的鬼神仍具有一种普遍的恐惧。 4. All the characters in this book are imaginary. 这本书中的人物都是虚构的。', '副词: imaginarily 名词: imaginariness 名词复数: imaginaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solo', '[\'soʊloʊ]', 'n.独奏；独唱 adj.单独的 adv.单独地 v.单独表演；[空]放单飞(飞行员一个人开飞机,无教练陪同)', '1. The first piece is a piano solo by Berio. 第一个节目是贝里奥的钢琴独奏。 2. The concert began with piano solo. 音乐会以一首钢琴独奏开始。 3. He has been asked to sing a solo at the concert. 他已被邀请在演奏会上表演独唱。 4. The student essayed his first solo flight. 该学员尝试作首次单独飞行。 5. His landing was awkward,but it was only the second time he\'d flown solo. 他的着陆技术很不熟练,但这只是他第二次单飞。', '名词复数: solos 过去式: soloed 过去分词: soloed 现在分词: soloing 第三人称单数: solos');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tread', '[tred]', 'n.步法；踏面；胎面花纹；鞋底 v.踩；行走；践踏；(鸟类)交配', '1. We heard his heavy tread on the staircase. 我们听到了他走在楼梯上沉重的脚步声。 2. We would hear the heavy, monotonous tread of the approaching bull. 我们能听到越来越近的公牛那沉重单调的蹄音。 3. Check your tire pressure and tread. 经常检查轮胎气压和胎面。 4. Driving with worn tread(s) can be dangerous. 轮胎胎面磨损的汽车开著有危险。 5. The cattle had trodden a path to the pond. 牛群踩出了一条通往池塘的小径。', '形容词: treadless 过去式: trod 过去分词: trodden/trod 现在分词: treading 第三人称单数: treads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wary', '[\'weri]', 'adj.小心的；机警的', '1. He was wary of telling state secrets. 他小心翼翼以免泄漏国家机密。 2. Hood was wary but he grew to trust her. 胡德一开始将信将疑，但后来信任她了。 3. Lucy learned at school about being wary of strangers. 露西在学校里学会了要提防陌生人。 4. She was wary of strangers. 她对陌生人很警惕。', '副词: warily 比较级: warier 最高级: wariest 名词: wariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('excess', '[ɪk\'ses]', 'n.超过；过量；过剩 adj.过量的；额外的', '1. Our school has a student number in excess of 800. 我们学校的学生数超过八百人。 2. His excesses at parties are well known. 尽人皆知他在聚会上十分放肆。 3. An excess of fat in one\'s diet can lead to heart disease. 食物中脂肪过多会导致心脏病。 4. This wave of excess density is sound. 这种过剩密度的波就是声波。 5. The fat boy went on a diet to get rid of his excess weight. 这个胖男孩节制饮食以减轻过量的体重。', '过去式: excessed 过去分词: excessed 现在分词: excessing 第三人称单数: excesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blame', '[bleɪm]', 'vt.责备；把 ... 归咎于 n.责备；过失', '1. The driver was not to blame for the accident. 这次事故怪不着司机。 2. The bank manager was really to blame, though he tried to pin it on a clerk. 真正受责备的应该是银行经理，可是他却想把责任推到一个职员身上。 3. She blamed him for the failure of their marriage. 她把婚姻的触礁归咎於他。 4. They blamed the rise in oil prices for the big increase in inflation. 他们把通货膨胀大幅度增长归咎于石油价格的上涨。 5. We were ready to take the blame for what had happened. 我们准备对所发生的事承担责任。', '名词: blamer 过去式: blamed 过去分词: blamed 现在分词: blaming 第三人称单数: blames');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grand', '[ɡrænd]', 'adj.重大的；豪华的；宏伟的；壮丽的 n.大钢琴；一千美元', '1. This is a grand occasion. 这是个盛大的场面。 2. He was born in the purple and was brought up in the grand palace. 他出身于皇族,在宏伟的宫殿中长大。 3. How grand the mountains look in the early evening! 暮色中群山是多么壮丽！ 4. The piano soon developed into the contemporary nine- to ten-foot concert grand. 不久钢琴就发展到同时代的九到十英尺的平台大钢琴。', '副词: grandly 比较级: grander 最高级: grandest 名词: grandness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('host', '[hoʊst]', 'n.主人；主持人；主办方；大量；寄主；主机 v.主办；主持；做东', '1. At the end of the party, we thanked our host and went back home. 宴会结束时,我们谢了主人后便回家去了。 2. He was the host for a TV talk show. 他是一名电视脱口秀的主持人。 3. Which country will be the host country for the next Olympic Games? 哪个国家将是下届奥运会的主办国？ 4. A host of friends met him at the railway station. 一大群朋友在火车站迎接他。 5. We sincerely wish China success in hosting Expo 2010. 我们衷心祝愿中国成功主办2010年世博会。', '形容词: hostly 过去式: hosted 过去分词: hosted 现在分词: hosting 第三人称单数: hosts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dimension', '[ˌdɪ\'menʃən]', 'n. 尺寸； 次元； 容积； 维度； 范围； 方面 vt. 标尺寸； 形成 ... 尺寸', '1. Height is an external dimension. 高是外部尺寸。 2. When a dimension\'s origin is in doubt use the datums specified. 当不能确定尺寸原点时，使用规定的基准。 3. The fifth dimension creates everything that is on earth. 第五次元创造了地球上所有的东西。 4. The crystal extractors from that dimension cross through all dimensions. 从那个次元的水晶提取器穿越所有的次元。 5. We were told to dimension off the plots. 吩咐我们在图表上标出尺寸。', '形容词: dimensional 副词: dimensionally 名词: dimensionality 过去式: dimensioned 过去分词: dimensioned 现在分词: dimensioning 第三人称单数: dimensions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impervious', '[ɪm\'pɜːrviəs]', 'adj.不能渗透的；不为所动的', '1. This material is impervious to rainwater. 这种材料防雨。 2. Rubber boots are impervious to water. 橡胶鞋是防水的。 3. He is impervious to criticism. 他对批评我行我素。', '副词: imperviously 名词: imperviousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exhale', '[eks\'heɪl]', 'v.呼气；散发', '1. Take a deep breath, then exhale slowly. 深吸一口气，然后慢慢呼气。 2. She exhaled slowly to show her annoyance. 她长叹以示厌烦。 3. He lit his cigar and exhaled smoke. 他点燃雪茄，然后吐出烟雾。 4. He exhaled the pungent odor of garlic. 他散发出刺鼻的大蒜味。', '过去式: exhaled 过去分词: exhaled 现在分词: exhaling 第三人称单数: exhales');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('belligerent', '[bə\'lɪdʒərənt]', 'adj.好战的；交战的 n.交战国；交战者', '1. Tom always said some very belligerent things. 汤姆他老是说些十分挑衅性的话。 2. The belligerent countries are having difficulties funding the war. 交战国在为战争提供资金上有困难。 3. The belligerents were due to try to settle their differences. 交战双方是由于试图解决他们之间的分歧。', '副词: belligerently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('urge', '[ɜːrdʒ]', 'vt.驱策；鼓励；催促；力陈 vi.极力主张 n.冲动；强烈愿望', '1. He urged the horses on with a whip. 他用鞭子策马前行。 2. Many physicians urge aerobic exercise. 很多医生鼓励有氧运动。 3. We will urge them to adhere to the Paris Agreement. 我们将敦促他们遵守巴黎协议。 4. They urged on us the need for cooperation. 他们向我们强调合作的必要性。 5. He urged against the adoption of the measure. 他极力反对采取这项措施。 6. I feel the urge to be outside when spring comes again. 当春天再次来临,我就有了到户外活动的冲动。', '过去式: urged 过去分词: urged 现在分词: urging 第三人称单数: urges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amalgamate', '[ə\'mælɡəmeɪt]', 'v.合并；混合', '1. Our local brewery has amalgamated with another firm. 我们本地的酿酒厂与另一个公司合并了。 2. There are plans to amalgamate the village school with a larger one nearby. 有计划让乡村学校和附近一所规模较大的学校合并。', '形容词: amalgamative 名词: amalgamator 过去式: amalgamated 过去分词: amalgamated 现在分词: amalgamating 第三人称单数: amalgamates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arbitrator', '[\'ɑːrbɪtreɪtər]', 'n.仲裁人；公断者', '1. The lead arbitrator was Swedish. 主仲裁人是位瑞典人。 2. The Chinese company picked a Chinese arbitrator. 这家中国公司选择了一位中国仲裁人。 3. The dispute shall be submitted for arbitration by a mutually nominated arbitrator. 这起纠纷应由一位双方共同指定的仲裁人提交仲裁。 4. If negotiations are deadlocked, an arbitrator must be called in. 如果谈判陷入僵局，就必须请一位仲裁人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ammonia', '[ə\'moʊniə]', 'n.氨；阿摩尼亚', '1. Tests of the manure showed a high ammonia content. 这种肥料经过化验表明氨的含量很高。 2. Dilute the ammonia with water before you use it. 使用氨之前用水稀释它。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adjacent', '[ə\'dʒeɪsnt]', 'adj.邻近的；毗连的；接近的', '1. The house adjacent to ours has been sold. 与我们家邻接的房子已经售出。 2. His house is adjacent to mine. 他的寓所与我的相毗连。 3. The planes landed on adjacent runways. 这些飞机在毗连的跑道上降落。 4. The island of Cuba is adjacent to Florida. 古巴岛接近佛罗里达。', '副词: adjacently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swallow', '[\'swɑːloʊ]', 'n.燕子；吞咽；一次吞咽的量 v.忍受；吞下；咽下；轻信；不流露感情；收回', '1. There are many swallows flying in the sky. 天空中有许多燕子。 2. The swallow has made a nest under our eaves. 燕子在我们的屋檐下垒了一个窝。 3. He downed the medicine at one swallow. 他一口便把药全吞下了。 4. Let me take a swallow of beer. 让我喝口啤酒。 5. They can\'t treat me like that; I\'m not going to swallow it. 他们不能这样对待我，我忍不下这口气。', '名词: swallower 过去式: swallowed 过去分词: swallowed 现在分词: swallowing 第三人称单数: swallows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amount', '[ə\'maʊnt]', 'n.数量；总额 vi.总计；等于', '1. A petrol gauge shows the amount of petrol left in a car. 汽油表指示出汽车里所剩的汽油数量。 2. He has a large amount of mail to answer every day. 他每天有大量的信件要回复。 3. Remember to tell the guest the amount of the bill. 记得告诉客人帐单的总额。 4. We charge one percent commission on the total amount. 我们收取支票总额的1%25作为手续费。 5. The total cost of repairs amounted to 100 dollars. 修理费用总计一百美元。', '过去式: amounted 过去分词: amounted 现在分词: amounting 第三人称单数: amounts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remnant', '[\'remnənt]', 'n.残余；残剩余；残存者；零头 adj.剩余的', '1. If something has been partly used or destroyed, we use remains or remnants. 若某物的一部分已用掉或毁掉，其剩余或残存部分可用。 2. I will sell this remnant to you, at cost. 我愿将此剩货照成本卖给你。 3. The remnants of last night\'s meal were still on the table. 昨天晚上的剩余物还在桌子上。 4. The Ainu settlers in Hokkaido are the last remnant of a prehistoric race. 北海道的阿伊努人是史前某个种族的最后残存者。 5. The beautiful curtain is made of remnant materials. 这个漂亮的窗帘是用零头布做的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('counteract', '[ˌkaʊntər\'ækt]', 'v.抵制；清除；中和；对抗', '1. We must counteract extremism in the party. 我们应该抵制党内的极端主义。 2. They will counteract the effects of his bad influence. 他们要清除他的不良影响。 3. We must try to counteract the present current of anti-government feeling. 我们应该努力消除目前的这股反政府情绪。 4. One way to counteract hard water is by using a water softener. 中和硬水的方法是使用软水剂。', '形容词: counteractive 副词: counteractively 名词: counteraction 过去式: counteracted 过去分词: counteracted 现在分词: counteracting 第三人称单数: counteracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aptitude', '[\'æptɪtuːd]', 'n.天资；资质；才能；倾向', '1. That student has an aptitude for mathematics. 那个学生有数学方面的天赋。 2. He shows great aptitude in painting. 他在绘画上表现出很高的才能。 3. He has little aptitude for a business career. 他没有从事商业的资质。 4. He has an aptitude for languages. 他具有学习语言的才能。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hackneyed', '[\'hæknid]', 'adj.（指词语﹑ 言辞等）陈腐的；老生常谈的 动词hackney的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. Yes, it\'s a hackneyed phrase, but politics is the art of the possible. 没错，这是一条陈腐的词语，但政治的确是一种可能事件的艺术。 2. The hackneyed phrase came unintended to his lips. 他顺口说了这句老掉牙的套话。 3. \"Last but not least\" is regarded as a hackneyed expression. “最后的但并非最不重要的一点“这个词组被认为是陈词烂调了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('centennial', '[sen\'teniəl]', 'n.百年纪念 adj.一百年的 =centenary(美).', '1. There are many centennial houses on the street. 街上有好多栋百年老屋。 2. Why we choose Centennial College? 为什么选择百年理工? 3. What else do you know about the Centennial State? 你还知道这个百年州的什麽事迹呢? 4. Conduct a Centennial Community Project. 进行一个百周年社区计划。', '副词: centennially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indigenous', '[ɪn\'dɪdʒənəs]', 'adj.土生土长的；本地的；天生的', '1. Indians were the indigenous inhabitants of America. 印第安人是美洲的土著居民。 2. Shinto is the natural indigenous religion of Japan. 日本之神道教是日本本土的自然教。 3. The indigenous population was soon displaced by the settlers. 没过多久，外来移民就把当地人赶出了家园。 4. Love and hate are emotions indigenous to all humanity. 爱兴恨是人类固有的感情。', '副词: indigenously 名词: indigenousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bidding', '[\'bɪdɪŋ]', 'n.出价；投标；命令 动词bid的现在分词形式.', '1. Our bidding is reasonable. 我们的出价是合理的。 2. He beat out another firm in bidding. 他在投标中击败另一家公司。 3. He often does his wife\'s bidding. 他经常按他妻子的吩咐去做。 4. Do my bidding, or feel the power of my wrath. 遵照我的命令，否则让你尝尝我的愤怒。 5. Several companies are bidding for the contract to build the bridge. 有几家公司在投标争取承包建桥工程。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('principle', '[\'prɪnsəpl]', 'n.原理；原则；主义；信念', '1. A bicycle and a motorcycle are built on the same principle. 自行车和摩托车是根据同样的原理制造的。 2. Archimedes ,a great physicist ,discovered the principle of floating bodies . 阿基米德，一位伟大的物理学家，发现了浮体原理。 3. We adhere to the principle that everyone should be treated fairly. 我们坚持人人都应该被平等对待这一原则。 4. It is easier to fight for one\'s principle than to live up to them. 为自己的主义斗争，要比他们施诸实践更容易。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('roughly', '[\'rʌfli]', 'adv.粗略地；大约；粗暴地；粗糙地；粗鲁地', '1. Roughly speaking, I would say that about100 people attended the exhibit. 粗略地说来，我想大约有100人参观了展览。 2. There were roughly 200 people there. 那里大约有两百人。 3. They all left at roughly the same time. 他们都是大约同一时间离开的。 4. The speaker was roughly handled by the mob. 演说者受到暴民的粗暴对待。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exhaust', '[ɪɡ\'zɔːst]', 'v.使筋疲力尽；耗尽；详尽论述 n.排气装置；废气', '1. Caring for young children can exhaust you physically and mentally. 照顾小孩子会使你身心疲惫。 2. The expedition was forced to turn back when it exhausted its food supply. 没有了食物,这个探险队不得不返航。 3. He failed to exhaust this subject. 他没能对这个题作详尽无遗的论述。 4. The car needs a new exhaust. 这辆车需要换一个新的排气管。', '形容词: exhaustible 副词: exhaustedly 名词: exhauster 过去式: exhausted 过去分词: exhausted 现在分词: exhausting 第三人称单数: exhausts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nectar', '[\'nektər]', 'n.花蜜；甜美的饮料；众神饮用的酒', '1. Nectar and pollen are very nutritious. 花蜜和花粉是很有营养的。 2. Bees gather nectar and make it into honey. 蜂采花蜜制成蜂蜜。 3. Even nectar is poison if taken to excess. 美酒过量也会变成毒药。 4. The wine is good, like drinking nectar. 这种酒真好喝, 好像琼浆玉液一般。', '形容词: nectarous');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ritual', '[\'rɪtʃuəl]', 'n.仪式；典礼；宗教仪式；固定程序 adj.仪式的；老规矩的；惯常的', '1. Don\'t be overly solemn or feel that you are taking part in some special ritual; 不要太严肃,或觉得自己正在进行某种仪式; 2. She objects to the ritual of organized religion. 她反对规范的宗教仪规。 3. A strange ritual was enacted before our eyes. 在我们眼前展现出一种奇特的仪式. 4. He performed his ablution before the ritual. 他在典礼前沐 5. So nightly baths have become a part of their ritual even to this day. 所以晚间沐浴成为他们结束一天仪式的一部分。', '副词: ritually');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dump', '[dʌmp]', 'vt.倾倒；抛弃；倾销；抛售；倾卸；[计]转储 vi.倾倒；突然落下 n.垃圾场；军需供应站', '1. Some people just dump their rubbish in the river. 有些人径直往河里倒垃圾。 2. Sealed containers of nuclear waste have been dumped in the sea. 盛有核废料的密封容器被丢在海里。 3. They dump surplus goods abroad. 他们向国外倾销过剩货物。 4. A complete memory dump file is rarely required. 通常很少需要完全内存转储文件。 5. You\'ll be fined if you dump here. 在这儿倒垃圾要被罚款的。 6. There is a refuse dump out of the town. 镇外有个垃圾场。', '名词: dumper 过去式: dumped 过去分词: dumped 现在分词: dumping 第三人称单数: dumps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('summit', '[\'sʌmɪt]', 'n.顶点；最高阶层', '1. It was a warm climb to the summit. 向顶峰攀登时身上都热起来了。 2. The Hungarian view is magnificent from the summit of the mountains. 从群山之颠看到的匈牙利景色非常壮丽。 3. The news is all about the latest summit meeting. 这条消息是关於最近的首脑级会议的。 4. He attained the summit of his ambition. 他达到了追求的最高目标。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invert', '[ɪn\'vɜːrt]', 'v.倒置；反转；颠倒 adj.转化的 n.颠倒物；[心]同性恋者', '1. The little boy caught the insect by inverting the cup over it. 小男孩把杯子倒过来就逮住了那只昆虫。 2. The chairs were inverted on the table. 椅子被倒置过来放在了桌子上。 3. Place a plate over the cake tin and invert it. 在蛋糕烤模上盖一个盘子，然后将其翻倒过来。 4. Please invert the word order in a sentence. 请把句中的词序颠倒下。', '形容词: invertible 过去式: inverted 过去分词: inverted 现在分词: inverting 第三人称单数: inverts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hatred', '[\'heɪtrɪd]', 'n.仇恨；憎恨；敌意；怨恨', '1. His words stirred up my hatred. 他的话激起了我的仇恨。 2. There is implacable hatred between the two nations. 两国之间有无法消除的仇恨。 3. This hatred was generated by racial prejudice. 这种仇恨是由种族偏见引起的。 4. I have a vehement hatred of people who is cruel to animal. 我对残害动物的人怀有强烈的憎恨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('observe', '[əb\'zɜːrv]', 'v.观察；遵守；注意到；庆祝', '1. We have to observe carefully what\'s going on there. 我们必须仔细观察那里的动静。 2. He made a telescope through which he could observe the stars. 他做了个望远镜,用其观察星座。 3. All citizens should observe traffic rules. 每位公民都应该遵守交通规则。 4. We should observe the proprieties. 我们应该遵守礼节。', '副词: observingly 过去式: observed 过去分词: observed 现在分词: observing 第三人称单数: observes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('warp', '[wɔːrp]', 'vt.使翘起；弄歪；歪曲 vi.变歪；扭曲 n.弯曲；歪曲；乖僻；经纱；绞船索', '1. The heat has warped the boards. 热使木板弯翘了。 2. His judgement was warped by self-interest. 他受私心影响判断不确。 3. Histories are often warped by biases. 历史常为偏见所曲解。 4. The window frames had begun to warp. 窗框已经开始变形。 5. There is a warp in the board. 这块木板有点弯曲。', '名词: warper 过去式: warped 过去分词: warped 现在分词: warping 第三人称单数: warps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rank', '[ræŋk]', 'n.等级；阶层；排；列 v.排列；分等级；列为；排名，排位 adj.繁茂的；讨厌的', '1. He is above me in rank. 他的级别比我高。 2. They are people of all ranks and classes. 他们来自各阶层各阶级。 3. Taxis stand in a taxi rank waiting to be hired. 出租汽车排成一行等人雇车。 4. The riot police quickly fell into rank for action. 防暴警察迅速列队准备行动。 5. Rank the states in the order of size. 按大小把这些州排列一下。', '副词: rankly 比较级: ranker 最高级: rankest 名词: rankness 过去式: ranked 过去分词: ranked 现在分词: ranking 第三人称单数: ranks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('account', '[ə\'kaʊnt]', 'n.账户；帐目；赊账；老主顾；报告；描述；解释；说明；估计；理由；利益；好处；根据 v.解释；导致；报账；把 ... 视为；归咎(于)', '1. She squared her account at the store. 她在商店里结清帐目。 2. We have accounts with most of our suppliers. 我们与大多数供应商都是实行赊购制。 3. The agency has lost several of its most important accounts. 这家代理机构失去了几家最重要的老客户。 4. This is a particular account of the accident. 这是一份全面而详尽的事故报告。 5. He has been asked to account for his conduct. 他被要求解释他的行为。', '过去式: accounted 过去分词: accounted 现在分词: accounting 第三人称单数: accounts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ebb', '[eb]', 'n.退潮；衰落 vi.落潮；衰退', '1. They started sailing on the ebb. 他们于退潮时出航了。 2. But the moments will never ebb away. 但那些瞬间永远不会退潮。 3. Private and public virtues were at the lowest ebb. 公德与私德均在衰落之中。 4. Manufacturing business is now at a low ebb. 制造业现正处于衰落中。 5. Fishing boats were standing down with the ebb. 渔船趁着落潮出航。', '过去式: ebbed 过去分词: ebbed 现在分词: ebbing 第三人称单数: ebbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nickel', '[\'nɪkl]', 'n.镍；镍币；五分镍币 vt.镀镍于', '1. Danish women have contact allergy caused by nickel. 丹麦妇女因镍造成接触性过敏症。 2. Bear ran over to Pig and bought another hot dog with the nickel. 熊跑到猪那，用这个五分镍币从猪那买了一个热狗。 3. America\'s best buy for a nickel is a telephone call to the right man. 在美国以一枚镍币可购得的最划算的东西，是打电话找到要找的人。 4. Each nickel is worth five cents. 每个五分镍币相当于5美分。 5. Screw plugs, brass nickel plated, with metric thread. 圆形螺旋塞，材质为黄铜镀镍，公制螺纹。', '过去式: nickeled/nickelled 过去分词: nickeled/nickelled 现在分词: nickeling/nickelling 第三人称单数: nickels/nickels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quiver', '[\'kwɪvər]', 'v.颤抖；振动 n.颤抖；箭袋；箭袋内的箭', '1. The old man quivered with rage. 这位老人气得发抖。 2. The skylark quivered its wings. 云雀抖动它的双翼。 3. There was a slight quiver in his voice as he spoke. 他说话时声音有些颤抖。 4. A quiver of fear ran through her. 一阵恐惧的颤抖传遍了她的全身。', '形容词: quivery 过去式: quivered 过去分词: quivered 现在分词: quivering 第三人称单数: quivers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immortal', '[ɪ\'mɔːrtl]', 'adj.不朽的；永世的 n.不朽的人物；神', '1. The spirits of the brave departed will be immortal. 英灵永在。 2. He left behind an immortal example to all posterity. 他给后世留下了不朽的典范。 3. Some people believe that the spirit is immortal. 有人相信灵魂不灭。 4. The little girl is very interested in the old legend of immortal creatures. 小女孩对有关永生的精灵的古老传奇非常感兴趣。 5. Shakespeare is one of the immortals. 莎士比亚是不朽的人物之一。', '副词: immortally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('objective', '[əb\'dʒektɪv]', 'adj.客观的；真实的；宾语的 n.目标；目的；[物]物镜；[语]宾语', '1. From any objective perspective,it is simply too long. 从客观的角度来讲，这实在是太长了。 2. She gives an objective report of what has happened. 她就发生的事情进行客观的报告。 3. He has told a story which sound not objective. 他讲了听起来不真实的一个故事。 4. Her principal objective was international fame as a scientist. 她的主要目标是当个有国际声誉的科学家。', '副词: objectively 名词: objectiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interstellar', '[ˌɪntər\'stelər]', 'adj.星际的', '1. These elements become part of the interstellar gas and dust. 这些元素成了星际气体和星际尘埃的一部分。 2. We have already launched slow and modest interstellar spacecraft. 我们已经开动了慢而水平低的星际航空器。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resident', '[\'rezɪdənt]', 'n.居民；住客；住院医生 adj.居住的', '1. The residents of the town are proud of its new library. 该镇的居民都为镇上新建的图书馆感到自豪。 2. I have been resident in this hotel for two weeks. 我已经在这家旅馆里住了两个星期了。 3. I would get the neurosurgery resident down here. 我想请神经外科住院医师下楼到这儿来。 4. This dove was resident with us all the year round. 这只鸽子一年到头居住在这里和我们为伴。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slide', '[slaɪd]', 'vi.滑动；下滑；滑入；悄悄地溜走 vt.使滑动 n.幻灯片；滑坡；滑动；雪崩', '1. If you pull this lever, the roof will slide back. 拉一下这根杆,顶就往后滑动。 2. The book slid off my knee. 书从我膝上滑落。 3. House values may begin to slide. 房价可能开始逐渐下降了。 4. I had to slide into base to avoid the tag. 我必须滑上垒以免被触杀。 5. We are to slide the box by exerting a force on it. 我们对箱子施加作用力，使它滑动。 6. After you type your comment you can move it around on the slide. 键入批注后,您可以在幻灯片中移动批注。', '过去式: slid 过去分词: slid 现在分词: sliding 第三人称单数: slides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gainsay', '[ˌɡeɪn\'seɪ]', 'v.否认；反驳', '1. She is a fine woman - that nobody can gainsay. 她是个好女人－无人能否认。 2. No one will gainsay his integrity. 没有人对他的正直有话可讲。 3. Beyond gainsay it is a genuine Rembrandt. 无可否认地，那是真的伦布兰特（的画）。 4. I will not gainsay love, called love forsooth. 我不想问：真有爱这回事吗？有就有吧--', '名词: gainsayer 过去式: gainsaid 过去分词: gainsaid 现在分词: gainsaying 第三人称单数: gainsays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hydrothermal', '[ˌhaɪdrə\'θɜːməl]', 'adj.水热作用的；热液的', '1. Mineralized hydrothermal water mainly originated from the atmospheric rainfall. 成矿热液的水主要来自大气降水。', '副词: hydrothermally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exception', '[ɪk\'sepʃn]', 'n.例外；不合规则；反对；[律]异议', '1. There is always an exception to any rule. 任何规律总有例外。 2. All students without exception must take the English examination. 所有的学生毫无例外，都必须参加英语考试。 3. The spelling of this word is an interesting exception to the rule. 这个词的拼写很有趣,是本规则的例外。 4. He took great exception to what I said. 他极力反对我的话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blip', '[blɪp]', 'n.（在雷达屏幕显示出的）物体光点；尖音信号 v.在录像磁带上抹去(所录的音)', '1. Suddenly the radar shows a blip orbiting up ahead. 突然间，有个影像出现在雷达银幕，显示有东西在上方盘旋。', '过去式: blipped 过去分词: blipped 现在分词: blipping 第三人称单数: blips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accomplice', '[ə\'kɑːmplɪs]', 'n.共犯；同谋；帮凶', '1. The man was suspected as an accomplice. 那个人被怀疑为共犯。 2. In the accomplice, abettors\' problems attract scholars most.So far, some problems of abettors are not solved, and fail to come to any agreement. 在共犯中，教唆犯的问题更是受到学者们的关注，但是关于教唆犯的一些问题至今没有解决，莫衷一是。 3. He is suspected as an accomplice. 他有同谋嫌疑。 4. He was shortly to be tried at Aix with his accomplice. 不久他就得在艾克斯和他的同谋女犯一同受审。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constitution', '[ˌkɒnstə\'tjuːʃən]', 'n.宪法；组织；体质；构成，组成，构造', '1. The President swore to uphold the constitution. 总统宣誓维护宪法。 2. The country\'s constitution embodies the ideals of freedom and equality. 这个国家的宪法体现了自由和平等的理想。 3. The constitution of a primitive society is not necessarily simple. 原始社会的结构并不一定就是简单的。 4. Hunger and disease had weakened his constitution. 他饥饿与疾病交加，体质已削弱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('celebrate', '[\'selɪbreɪt]', 'v.庆祝；庆贺；颂扬', '1. Let\'s celebrate! 让我们好好庆祝一下吧！ 2. People in the city held a great party to celebrate their victory. 本市的市民举行了盛大的晚会庆祝他们的胜利。 3. They had a family feast to celebrate it. 他们举办家宴以示庆贺。 4. He read us a sonnet that celebrates love. 他给我们读了一首歌颂爱情的十四行诗。', '形容词: celebratory 名词: celebration 过去式: celebrated 过去分词: celebrated 现在分词: celebrating 第三人称单数: celebrates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('material', '[mə\'tɪriəl]', 'n.材料；原料；素材；资料；题材；物质 adj.物质的；重要的；关键的；肉体上的；实质性的', '1. The colour in this silk material will not fade. 这种绸布料子不会褪色。 2. The workshop has shut down for lack of raw material. 由于缺乏原料，这个车间已停工了。 3. She\'s collecting materials for her latest novel. 她在为其最新的小说收集素材。 4. He was grubbing about in the public library for materials. 他正在公共图书馆里寻找资料。 5. Material wealth doesn\'t equal spiritual wealth. 物质的财富并不代表精神的财富!', '名词: materialness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scale', '[skeɪl]', 'n.刻度；等级，规模；音阶；量程；天枰，磅秤；鳞片，鳞状物 v.攀登；按比例决定；称重；刮鳞；剥落', '1. How much does it read on the scale? 刻度显示的是多少? 2. The force of the wind is measured on a standard scale of 0-12. 风力是按0-12级标准等级测量的。 3. The fifth note of a scale is called a dominant. 音阶的第五音被称为属音。 4. It takes courage and strength to scale these cliffs. 攀登这些悬崖需要勇气和力量。', '形容词: scalelike 过去式: scaled 过去分词: scaled 现在分词: scaling 第三人称单数: scales');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prestige', '[pre\'stiːʒ]', 'n.[U]威望；声望 adj.有威信的；名贵的', '1. She enjoyed high prestige among the masses. 她在群众中享有很高威信。 2. He is an author of international prestige. 他是有国际声望的作家。 3. The old universities of Oxford and Cambridge still have a lot of prestige. 历史悠久的牛津大学和剑桥大学仍然享有很高的声望。 4. The company would do anything but risk their prestige at stake. 公司绝不愿将自己的信誉孤注一掷。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('require', '[rɪ\'kwaɪər]', 'v.要求；需要；命令；规定', '1. The director required that we should work all night. 主任要求我们通宵工作。 2. We must not propagate one method and require all localities to adopt it. 我们在宣传上不要只讲一种办法，要求各地都照着去做。 3. Please call if you require assistance. 如果需要帮忙，请打电话。 4. This game requires a minimum of three players. 这个游戏至少需要三个人才可以玩。', '形容词: requirable 名词: requirer 过去式: required 过去分词: required 现在分词: requiring 第三人称单数: requires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aggressive', '[ə\'ɡresɪv]', 'adj.侵略的；进攻性的；好斗的；有进取心的', '1. He has an aggressive manner. 他的态度咄咄逼人。 2. His style of argument in meetings is not so much aggressive as pertinacious. 他在会议上的辩论态度并非锋芒逼人而是坚持己见。 3. Red fire ants are very aggressive and readily attack anything that disturb them. 红火蚁攻击性强,容易攻击任何干扰它们的生物。 4. America has a lot of aggressive weapons now. 美国现在有很多进攻性武器。', '副词: aggressively 名词: aggressiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('asteroid', '[\'æstərɔɪd]', 'n.小行星；海盘车 adj.星状的', '1. This asteroid takes 238 years to orbit the sun. 这颗小行星需要花238年绕太阳运行一周。 2. Asteroid lies between Mars and Jupiter. 小行星位于火星与木星之间。 3. But he wanted to locate the impact site of the asteroid. 但是他想确定小行星的撞击地点. 4. Large meteorites actually come from the asteroid belt. 大型陨星实际上是来自小行星带。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adversity', '[əd\'vɜːrsəti]', 'n.不幸；灾难；逆境', '1. Hardship disposes man to meet adversity. 艰苦能让人适应逆境。 2. His struggle with adversity is fruitless. 他徒与不幸挣扎而毫无结果。 3. A genuine friend will not desert you in time of adversity. 真正的朋友不会在患难时弃你而去。 4. It is wise even in adversity to listen to reason. 灾难中听从理性的召唤也是明智的。', '名词复数: adversities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impart', '[ɪm\'pɑːrt]', 'vt.传授；赋予；告知', '1. A teacher\'s aim is to impart knowledge. 教师的作用是传授知识。 2. They had come to impart their experience in stock raising. 他们是来传授饲养牲畜的经验的。 3. The red curtains impart a certain elegance to the room. 红色的窗帘使房间平添几分雅致。 4. Your presence will impart an air of elegance to the party. 您的光临将会为宴会增添优雅的气氛。', '过去式: imparted 过去分词: imparted 现在分词: imparting 第三人称单数: imparts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incident', '[\'ɪnsɪdənt]', 'n.事变；事件；插曲 adj.难免的；附带的', '1. The serious incident along the border increased our fears of the war. 边境上的紧张局势加重了我们对战争的忧虑。 2. She couldn\'t erase the incident from her memory. 她难以忘记那次事件。 3. The police are connecting this incident with last week\'s terrorist bombing. 警方认为这次事件和上周的恐怖分子爆炸事件有关。 4. The incident put a dampener on his birthday party. 这件事使得他的生日晚会很扫兴。 5. These diseases are incident to childhood. 儿童易患这类疾病。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crown', '[kraʊn]', 'n.王冠；王权；花冠；顶点；齿冠；克朗（丹麦、瑞典、捷克等国的货币单位） vt.加冕；使 ... 成王；居 ... 之顶；镶齿冠；使圆满；<口>打…的头部', '1. The crown was enchased with gold and silver. 这顶王冠上镶嵌着金和银。 2. She refused the crown. 她拒不接受王位。 3. I know she promised him a lilac crown. 我知道,她曾允诺他一顶紫丁香的花冠。 4. He cracked his crown on a microphone during a performance. 他在一次表演中在麦克风上把齿冠打破了。 5. They wanted to crown Caesar king . 他们想立凯撒为王。', '过去式: crowned 过去分词: crowned 现在分词: crowning 第三人称单数: crowns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entangle', '[ɪn\'tæŋɡl]', 'vt. 使 ... 纠缠； 使 ... 复杂； 卷入； 使 ... 混乱', '1. By equating it to killing babies they entangle the science in the politics of abortion. 通过将其等同于杀死婴儿，他们把科学卷入堕胎政治当中。', '名词: entanglement 过去式: entangled 过去分词: entangled 现在分词: entangling 第三人称单数: entangles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('characteristic', '[ˌkærəktə\'rɪstɪk]', 'n.特点；特性；特色 adj.典型的；特有的', '1. Ambition is a characteristic of all successful businessmen. 雄心勃勃是所有成功生意人的共同特点。 2. Kindness is one of his characteristics. 和善是他的特性之一。 3. A characteristic of the camel is its ability to live for a long time without water. 骆驼的特点是不喝水也能活很长时间。 4. They have been affected by trends in Italy too much to keep their own characteristics. 他们受意大利潮流的影响太大了,以致无法保持自己的特色。 5. It is the characteristic attitude of people towards life in those post-war years. 这是战后人们典型的处世态度。', '副词: characteristically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hideous', '[\'hɪdiəs]', 'adj.丑陋的；可怕的；可憎的；令人惊骇的', '1. They wear hideous clothes to cover their mostly monstrous bodies. 他们穿着丑陋的衣服以便掩盖畸形的身躯。 2. As punishment, she transformed him into a hideous beast and placed a spell on everyone in the castle. 为了惩罚王子，她把王子变成了一头丑陋的野兽，还对城堡里的每个人都施了魔法。 3. The hideous tale made the children cry. 那个可怕的故事把孩子们吓哭了。 4. I had walked straight into a hideous trap. 我一下子踏进了一个可怕的陷阱里。', '副词: hideously 名词: hideosity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('preliminary', '[prɪ\'lɪmɪneri]', 'adj.初步的；预备的；开始的 n.初步行动；准备；初步措施', '1. They have made a preliminary investigation. 他们已经做了初步的调查。 2. Our team got beaten in the preliminary rounds of the competition. 我们队在这次比赛的预赛中遭淘汰。 3. Movies at the preliminary stage were silent. 电影在初期是无声的。 4. There are a lot of preliminaries to be gone through before you can visit a foreign country. 在出访外国之前要做好许多准备工作。', '副词: preliminarily 名词复数: preliminaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beaver', '[\'biːvər]', 'n. 海狸； 獭皮(帽)； <粗>女性生殖器 n. 护面甲 vi. 卖力地工作', '1. The Indians would barter beaver pelts for weapons. 印第安人愿用海狸毛皮交换武器。 2. A Finnish man survived an attack by a beaver. 一名芬兰男子侥幸逃过一只海狸的攻击。', '过去式: beavered 过去分词: beavered 现在分词: beavering 第三人称单数: beavers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pertinent', '[\'pɜːrtnənt]', 'adj.中肯的；相关的；切题的；恰当的', '1. The expert made some pertinent comments on the scheme. 那专家对规划提出了一些中肯的意见。 2. He raised several pertinent questions. 他提了几个有关的问题。 3. The lawyer wanted to know all the details pertinent to the case. 律师想知道与该案有关的全部细节。 4. His answer was highly pertinent to the question. 他的回答非常切题。', '副词: pertinently 名词: pertinence');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assemble', '[ə\'sembl]', 'v.集合；收集；装配', '1. The students assembled in the school garden. 学生们在校园集合。 2. If the fire-alarm goes, staff should assemble outside the building. 火警警报响时全体人员应到楼外集合。 3. Assemble your papers and put them in the file . 把你们的论文收集起来归档。 4. The processing and assemble business is a component part of our foreign trade. 加工和装配贸易是我国对外贸易的一个组成部分。', '过去式: assembled 过去分词: assembled 现在分词: assembling 第三人称单数: assembles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('molten', '[\'moʊltən]', 'adj.熔化的；炽热的；铸造的 melt的过去分词.', '1. The molten metal was run into a mould. 熔化的金属被倒进模内。 2. The rising sun danced in water like molten gold. 初升的太阳犹如熔化的金子在水中荡漾。 3. Deep inside the Earth are very hot molten rocks called lava. 地球内部深处是十分炽热的岩浆的岩石熔化物。 4. As the plates separate, hot molten mantle material flows up to fill the void. 随着板块的分开，炽热的熔融地幔物质向上流动，以填充空隙。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quiz', '[kwɪz]', 'n.恶作剧；测验；问答比赛 v.盘问；对 ... 进行测验', '1. I hate the quiz someone made. 我讨厌别人搞恶作剧。 2. We will have a quiz tomorrow morning. 我们明天早晨进行一个小测验。 3. He asked us to prepare for a quiz. 他要我们准备好测验。 4. Match your skill against the experts in this quiz. 在这一测验中你与专家较量一下技巧吧。 5. Four men are being quizzed by police about the murder. 警察就这起谋杀案正在盘问四个男子。', '名词: quizzer 名词复数: quizzes 过去式: quizzed 过去分词: quizzed 现在分词: quizzing 第三人称单数: quizzes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('percussion', '[pər\'kʌʃn]', 'n.碰撞；打击乐器；[医]叩诊', '1. In an orchestra, people who play percussion instruments sit at the back. 在管弦乐队中，演奏打击乐器的人会坐在后面。 2. The next day, the woodwind, brass, and percussion of the orchestra joined us. 次日，管弦乐队的木管乐器、铜管乐器和打击乐器与我们合练。 3. For example, it makes percussion instruments out of general household items like pots, pans, and plastic hoses. 举例来说，他们将盆子、锅子及塑胶水管等一般家庭用品当成打击乐器。 4. The emphasis on percussion and Cuban rhythms make the style quite danceable and accessible. 它对于打击乐器和古巴旋律的偏重,使得这一音乐形式相当适合于跳舞,且易于理解。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elegant', '[\'elɪɡənt]', 'adj.优雅的；雅致的', '1. He strolled about, looking very debonair in his elegant new suit. 他穿了一身讲究的新衣服逛来逛去，显得颇为惬意。 2. He proudly promenaded his elegant companion in the park. 他得意地领著他那标致的伴侣遛公园。 3. We all wonder how you always look so young and beautiful and elegant! 我们都很想知道,为什么你总是那么优雅年轻。 4. The lady wears an elegant dark suit. 那位女士穿着雅致的深色套装。', '副词: elegantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gymnasium', '[dʒɪm\'neɪziəm]', 'n.体育馆；健身房 (复数）gymnasia或gymnasiums.', '1. The child somersaulted across the gymnasium. 那孩子翻著跟头从体育馆这头翻到那头。 2. A new gymnasium has been built on our campus. 我们大学的校园里新建了一座体育馆。 3. Our gymnasium lacks sports facilities. 我们的健身房缺少运动器材。 4. He go to the gymnasium to practise every day. 他每天都去健身房训练。', '名词复数: gymnasiums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('primary', '[\'praɪmeri]', 'adj.首要的；主要的；初级的；初等教育的；根本的；初期的 n.第一位；初选；最主要者；要素；原色；初级线圈', '1. The primary task for socialism is to develop the productive forces. 社会主义的首要任务是发展社会生产力。 2. Another primary reason is that there seems to be too many private cars and not enough public buses. 另一个主要原因是私家车过多而公交车不够。 3. The demand for primary products is on the increase in European market. 欧洲市场对初级产品的需求在增长。 4. Primary education comes under the umbrella of local government. 小学教育受地方政府的保护。 5. We should place development on the primary in governing and rejuvenating the country. 我们应将发展放在执政兴国中的第一位。', '名词复数: primaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defend', '[dɪ\'fend]', 'v.防守；防护；辩护', '1. Some players are better at defending. 有些运动员较擅长打防卫。 2. The union said that they would take action to defend their member\'s jobs. 工会说他们将采取行动维护会员的工作权益。 3. He was afraid of being attacked by Liu Bei and Sun Quan, so he sent a troop to defend Jingzhou. 他害怕刘备和孙权继续向他进攻,派人在荆州防守。 4. She demonstrated how best to defend oneself. 她示范最有效的自卫方法。', '形容词: defendable 名词: defender 过去式: defended 过去分词: defended 现在分词: defending 第三人称单数: defends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mean', '[miːn]', 'v.意思是；打算；导致；意味 adj.低劣的；刻薄的；卑鄙的；出色的；吝啬的；平均的；中等的 n.平均值；平均数；中间；中庸', '1. What does this word mean? 这个单词是什么意思？ 2. I mean that\'s his own decision to resign or not. 我的意思是说辞不辞职是他自己的决定。 3. I mean to call on you tomorrow. 我打算明天看望你。 4. His father meant him to be an engineer. 他父亲打算让他当工程师。 5. Don\'t be so mean to your little brother! 别对你弟弟那麽刻薄！ 6. It is an estimate of the mean of the population. 这是对人口平均数的一个估计。', '副词: meanly 比较级: meaner 最高级: meanest 过去式: meant 过去分词: meant 现在分词: meaning 第三人称单数: means');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('permissible', '[pər\'mɪsəbl]', 'adj.可允许的；容许的', '1. Our basic idea is to make use of the permissible clock skew to enhance the timing reliability of a circuit. 我们的基本想法，是利用可允许的时序差异值来提高电路的时序可靠度。 2. Level transmitters to automatically turn off the unloading compressors to prevent ammonia from exceeding the highest or maximum permissible level. 水平变送器自动地关闭卸料压缩机以阻止氨超过最高或可允许的最大高度值。 3. It is not only permissible but praiseworthy to want to benefit your own family by your own efforts. 希望通过自己努力发家致富的意愿，不仅是容许的，而且是值得赞扬的。', '副词: permissibly 名词: permissibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('metabolism', '[mə\'tæbəlɪzəm]', 'n.新陈代谢', '1. Their rate of metabolism may slow down. 他们的新陈代谢率可能会降低。 2. I do exercise every day to increase my metabolism. 我每天运动以促进新陈代谢。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intriguing', '[ɪn\'triːɡɪŋ]', 'adj.吸引人的；有趣的', '1. The bigger picture is more intriguing. 图片越大就越吸引人。 2. One could turn out to be quite intriguing to you. 其中的一个可能会成为非常吸引你的人。 3. It gave me an intriguing window into the way people live. 这为我提供了一个了解人们的生活方式的有趣窗口。 4. Some versions included intriguing details. 有些传说包括了使人迷惑的细节。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sarcasm', '[\'sɑːrkæzəm]', 'n.挖苦；讽刺', '1. This is no time to indulge in sarcasm. 现在可不是一味讽刺挖苦的时候。 2. His book commingles sarcasm and sadness. 他的作品混合了挖苦和悲伤。 3. He always spoke with a trace of sarcasm. 他说话总带着一丝讽刺。 4. This is no time to indulge in sarcasm. 现在可不是一味讽刺挖苦的时候。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stress', '[stres]', 'n.压力；强调；重音 vt.强调；重读', '1. Stress can be extremely damaging to your health. 压力对你的健康会是非常有害的。 2. The stress on setting an example is particularly necessary at present. 现在，强调以身作则这个问题很必要。 3. Which syllable does the stress of this word fall on? 这个单词的重音是在哪个音节上? 4. Here I will stress the importance of mathematics to the whole of science. 这里我要强调数学对整个科学的重要性。', '过去式: stressed 过去分词: stressed 现在分词: stressing 第三人称单数: stresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crafty', '[\'kræfti]', 'adj.狡猾的；熟练的；巧妙的', '1. They are crafty politicians. 他们是群老奸巨滑的政客。 2. He\'s a crafty old fox. 他是一只狡猾的老狐狸。 3. This crafty man is nothing but a crook. 那个狡猾的人纯粹是个骗子。 4. This fellow is very crafty; we had better be on our guard. 这个家伙诡计多端， 我们可得小心点儿。', '副词: craftily 比较级: craftier 最高级: craftiest 名词: craftiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fictitious', '[fɪk\'tɪʃəs]', 'adj.假想的；虚假的；虚伪的', '1. Hamlet was a fictitious character. 哈姆莱特是一个虚构的人物。 2. The characters in this story are all fictitious. 这个故事里的人物都是假想的。 3. The account he gives of his childhood is quite fictitious. 他把童年往事说得很假。 4. He greeted me with a fictitious enthusiasm. 他用虚伪的热情跟我打招呼。', '副词: fictitiously 名词: fictitiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genre', '[\'ʒɑːnrə]', 'n.类型；流派', '1. My favorite music genre is blues. 我最喜欢的音乐种类是蓝调。 2. What genre does the movie fall into---comedy or tragedy? 这部电影是什么风格?喜剧还是悲剧? 3. Later musicians created works based on this genre. 后来乐工也模仿创作曲子。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ignite', '[ɪɡ\'naɪt]', 'vi.着火；燃烧 vt.点燃；使 ... 燃烧；引发', '1. Large pieces of wood do not ignite easily. 大块木材是不易着火的。 2. Ammonia-air mixtures are quite difficult to ignite. 氨与空气的混合气体不易燃烧。 3. The burning gases can ignite the lean mixture. 燃烧着的气体能点燃稀的混合气。 4. What can you do to ignite your own passion? 有什么办法可以点燃你的热情？', '形容词: ignitable 名词: igniter 过去式: ignited 过去分词: ignited 现在分词: igniting 第三人称单数: ignites');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spacious', '[\'speɪʃəs]', 'adj.宽敞的；广阔的', '1. The hotel is neither spacious nor comfortable. 这旅馆既不宽敞也不舒服。 2. The systematic arrangement of chairs makes the hall look spacious. 座椅按照顺序排列，这使得礼堂里显得很宽敞。 3. In its spacious halls are displayed over8000 priceless relics. 在它宽敞的大厅里，展出了8000多件珍贵文物。 4. The museum is complemented by a spacious garden. 广大宽阔的庭院为博物馆增色不少。', '副词: spaciously 名词: spaciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('linger', '[\'lɪŋɡər]', 'vi.徘徊；逗留；消磨；漫步', '1. The beautiful melody is lingering in my mind. 美妙的音乐在我心中回荡。 2. She linger after the concert, hoping to meet the star. 音乐会后她徘徊不去，希望能遇见明星。 3. He made excuses to linger on the stairs. 他找借口故意在楼梯口上磨磨蹭蹭。 4. We can\'t linger any more, because we have so many works unfinished. 我们有这么作业还没完成,不能在拖延了。', '副词: lingeringly 名词: lingerer 过去式: lingered 过去分词: lingered 现在分词: lingering 第三人称单数: lingers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quality', '[\'kwɑːləti]', 'n.品质；才能；特质 adj.高品质的；<英俚>棒极了', '1. He examined the quality of the furniture carefully. 他仔细检查家俱的品质。 2. Her most essential quality is kindness. 她最主要的品质是善良。 3. He shows quality of leadership. 他显示出领导才能。 4. What are the qualities that mark a great leader ? 伟大领袖的特质是什么? 5. Even the best quality rubber will perish with age. 就是最佳质量的橡胶也会因老化而腐烂。', '名词复数: qualities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resolve', '[rɪ\'zɑːlv]', 'vt.解决；决定；表决；分解 vi.决定；分解 n.决心；坚决', '1. Intensive efforts are being made to resolve the dispute. 现正全力以赴来解决这场纠纷。 2. He resolved that nothing should hold him back. 他下决心不让任何事情阻挡他。 3. We can resolve the problem into more elementary items. 我们能够把这个问题分解成更基本的细目。 4. He resolved on going abroad to study. 他决定到海外留学。 5. He kept his resolve to do better. 他决心干得更出色。', '形容词: resolvable 副词: resolvedly 名词: resolvability 过去式: resolved 过去分词: resolved 现在分词: resolving 第三人称单数: resolves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('musical', '[\'mjuːzɪkl]', 'adj.音乐的；喜欢音乐的；悦耳的 n.音乐片', '1. The mother found that her son had a musical talent. 母亲发现儿子有音乐天赋。 2. Since he can play many musical instruments, he may well be called a man of accomplishments. 他能演奏许多乐器，当然称得上是个多才多艺的人。 3. Everyone in my family is very musical. 我家所有人都很喜欢音乐。 4. A musical bell softly sounded somewhere in the passageway. 走廊的某处响起轻柔悦耳的铃声。 5. Carroll appeared in a number of Broadway musicals. 卡洛尔演出了一系列百老汇音乐剧。', '副词: musically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sensible', '[\'sensəbl]', 'adj.明智的；合情理的；可觉察的；实际的 n.可感知物', '1. To wink at rudeness in children is not sensible. 对小孩粗鲁的行为视若无睹是不明智的。 2. That sounds very sensible to me. 我觉得这很合理。 3. Saving your presence, I don\'t think the suggestion is very sensible. 请恕我直言，我认为这个建议不太合情理。 4. Her distress was sensible from her manner. 她的悲痛从她的态度上可觉察到。 5. The world of dreams is our real world whilst we are sleeping because our attention then lapses from the sensible world. 在睡眠中梦见的世界便是我们的真实世界，因为那时我们的注意力已从可感知世界转移开。', '副词: sensibly 名词: sensibleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quit', '[kwɪt]', 'v.停止；离开；退出；辞职', '1. You must quit smoking. Most important of all, you should start taking exercise. 你必须戒烟，更重要的是，你该开始运动。 2. They have to quit China in a few days. 他们必须在几天之内离开中国。 3. The guard did not quit his post all night long. 那个哨兵整夜都没有离开他的哨位。 4. Some students quit school due to poverty. 一些学生因贫困而辍学。', '过去式: quit/quitted 过去分词: quit/quitted 现在分词: quitting 第三人称单数: quits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('epoch', '[\'epək]', 'n. 时期； 时代； 新纪元； 划时代的大事； <地质>世', '1. Ice age refers to the latest glacial epoch. 冰河时期指的是最近的一个冰川时期。 2. The Revolution had many of these men, proportioned to the epoch. 革命时期有过许多那样的人，都和那时代相称。 3. Einstein\'s theory marked a new epoch in history. 爱因斯坦的理论标志著历史上一个新时代的开始。 4. The epoch of revolution creates great figures. 革命时代造就伟大的人物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consonant', '[\'kɑːnsənənt]', 'n.辅音 adj.一致的；符合的；辅音的', '1. She asked me to pronounce each vowel and consonant clearly. 她叫我把每个元音和辅音都清晰地发出来。 2. Many letters in the alphabet such as b, c, d, etc are consonants. 字母表中的许多字母像b，c，d，等等都是辅音字母。 3. His view on the issue is consonant with mine. 他对这个问题的看法和我是一致的。 4. The quality of this suit is not quite consonant with its price . 这套衣服的质量与价钱不太相符。', '副词: consonantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pueblo', '[\'pwebloʊ]', 'Pueblo: n.；普艾布罗(美国科罗拉多州中部一城市) pueblo: n.；普埃布洛族；普埃布洛人', '1. A Pueblo people located north-northeast of Santa Fe, New Mexico. 陶斯人一支居住于美国新墨西哥州圣大菲城东北偏北的普埃布洛印地安人中的成员 2. A pueblo of northern New Mexico northeast of the town of Taos. Population, 1,030. 陶斯美国新墨西哥州北部一村庄，位于陶斯镇的东北。人口1, 030', '名词复数: pueblos');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overcome', '[ˌoʊvər\'kʌm]', 'vt.战胜；克服；使受不了；(感情等)压倒 vi.获胜；赢', '1. I realized that there is no way I can overcome it. 我意识到自己没有办法战胜它。 2. There will be no difficulty in the world that they cannot overcome. 世界上任何困难他们都可以克服。 3. We can and must overcome our shortcomings. 我们能够而且必须克服我们的缺点。 4. He was overcome by the gas fumes. 汽油味使他受不了。 5. We shall overcome! 我们一定胜利！', '过去式: overcame 过去分词: overcome 现在分词: overcoming 第三人称单数: overcomes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('action', '[\'ækʃn]', 'n.行为；活动；措施；效用；交战；情节；事件；姿态；起诉；机能', '1. There is no denying that your action has affected her normal life. 不可否认,你的行为已经影响了她的正常生活。 2. After the security incident, you should create an action report that includes three simple goals. 这次安全事故后,你要撰写一个包括三个简单目标的活动报告。 3. The government finally took some actions because the public had been pressing for inquiry into the question. 由于公众一再坚持调查这一问题,政府终于采取了一些措施。 4. The medicine will not take action until two hours later. 这药在两小时後才会起作用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affluent', '[\'æfluənt]', 'adj.富裕的 n.支流', '1. We live in an affluent society . 我们生活在一个富裕的社会中。 2. He was born to an affluent family. 他生在富裕人家。 3. A car and a house are considered as necessities in an affluent society. 在一个富裕的社会里,汽车和洋房都被当作是必需品。', '副词: affluently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('merchandise', '[\'mɜːrtʃəndaɪs]', 'n.商品；货物 v.推销；销售；经营', '1. Do you know the trade name of this box of merchandise? 你知道这箱商品的商标吗? 2. Among all the merchandise, I was interested in the cotton piece in particular. 在所有商品中，我对棉布特别感兴趣。 3. Their merchandise is of high quality. 他们的货物质量很好。 4. The merchandise is not up to standard. 货物品质未达标准。 5. We merchandise our furniture by advertising in newspapers. 我们在报上登广告推销家具.', '形容词: merchandisable 名词: merchandiser');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beam', '[biːm]', 'vi.微笑；发光 vt.播送；发射；用梁支撑 n.桁条；光线；(光线的)束；(横)梁', '1. She beamed at me. 她对我微笑。 2. His face(He) is beaming with delight. 他高兴得笑容满面。 3. From a sky of untarnished blue the sun beamed down upon Beijing. 阳光透过万里碧空照耀着北京城。 4. Television began beaming the national nominating conventions into the homes of Americans. 电视开始向美国家庭播放总统候选人全国提名大会的情况。 5. A rotary table helps to optimize the beam incidence angle. 一张旋转的桌子有助于将光线影响之方式角最佳化。', '过去式: beamed 过去分词: beamed 现在分词: beaming 第三人称单数: beams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accord', '[ə\'kɔːrd]', 'n.协议；一致；符合 v.与...一致；给予；调解', '1. The two countries reached an accord. 两国签订了一项协议。 2. His words are in accord with his ideas. 他心口一致。 3. Their views were found to be in perfect accord. 人们发现他们的意见是完全一致的。 4. Your behavior is not in accord with your principle. 你的行为与你的原则不符。 5. Our information does not accord with his reports. 我们所了解的情况与他的报告不一致。', '过去式: accorded 过去分词: accorded 现在分词: according 第三人称单数: accords');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disturbance', '[dɪ\'stɜːrbəns]', 'n.扰乱；骚动', '1. He was imprisoned for creating public disturbance. 他因扰乱公共治安而坐牢。 2. The drunken man was run in for creating a public disturbance. 那个醉汉因扰乱公共秩序而被拘留。 3. They were charged by the police with causing a disturbance. 他们被警方控告引起骚动。 4. The noise of cars passing along the road is a continual disturbance to our quiet at home. 马路上来往的车辆声音不断地破坏我们家的安宁。', '动词: disturb 形容词: disturbing 副词: disturbingly 名词复数: disturbances');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idiotic', '[ˌɪdi\'ɑːtɪk]', 'adj.愚蠢的', '1. Such an idiotic custom is still kept in that tribe. 那个部落仍保持着这种愚蠢的习惯。 2. She felt consumed with the most idiotic resentment. 她不断受到最愚蠢怨恨的折磨。', '副词: idiotically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('execute', '[\'eksɪkjuːt]', 'vt.执行；实行；处决；完成', '1. Congress makes the laws; the President executes them. 国会制定法律，总统执行法律。 2. We then execute the code that we want to test. 接下来,我们执行我们要测试的代码。 3. Now that we have made the decision, we may execute the scheme as previously agreed. 既然我们已经做了决定,我们就可以实行既定方案了。 4. They executed the king. 他们把国王处决了。', '形容词: executable 名词: executer 过去式: executed 过去分词: executed 现在分词: executing 第三人称单数: executes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agitate', '[\'ædʒɪteɪt]', 'v.煽动；搅动；焦虑', '1. They sent agents to agitate the local people. 他们派遣情报人员煽动当地的民众。 2. Agitate the mixture to dissolve the powder. 搅动混合物而使粉末溶化。 3. He was agitated about his wife\'s health. 他为他妻子的健康感到不安。 4. He became quite agitated when he was asked about his criminal past. 当问到他过去的犯罪历史时，他变得十分焦虑不安。', '形容词: agitative 副词: agitatedly 过去式: agitated 过去分词: agitated 现在分词: agitating 第三人称单数: agitates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('semester', '[sɪ\'mestər]', 'n.学期', '1. His writing has improved greatly in this semester. 这学期他的写作有了很大进步。 2. This semester will be my last one in this university. 这个学期将是我在这所大学的最后一学期了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('access', '[\'ækses]', 'n.入口；通道 n.接近(的机会)；使用之权 vt.进入；(电脑)存取', '1. This is the only means of access to the building. 这是进入这栋楼的唯一入口。 2. The avalanche cut off the access to the mountain village. 雪崩切断了进入山村的通道。 3. The only access to that building is along the track. 到那座大楼的唯一通道就是沿这条小路走。 4. Only high officials have access to the president. 只有高级官员才可以接近总统。 5. An error occurred when we tried to access the inventory database. 当我们试图进入存货数据库时，屏幕上显示出现了错误。', '过去式: accessed 过去分词: accessed 现在分词: accessing 第三人称单数: accesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wasp', '[wɑːsp]', 'n.黄蜂；胡蜂', '1. We can see the wasp to penetrate glass. 透过玻璃我们可以看到黄蜂。 2. Her face was covered in wasp stings. 她脸上满是黄蜂蜇过的伤痕。 3. Through the glass we can see the wasp. 透过玻璃我们可以看到胡蜂。 4. Vespa velutina nigrithorax is the main wasp species to sting residents in the city zone of Hangzhou. 墨胸胡蜂为杭州市城区的主要螫人毒蜂种类。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('depress', '[dɪ\'pres]', 'vt.使沮丧；压下；使萧条；降低；压抑', '1. He was depressed by his defeat. 失败让他沮丧。 2. The thought of having to take the exam again depressed me. 想到还需重新考试，我就感到沮丧。 3. The rainy days always depress me. 雨天总是使我沮丧。 4. Depress this button to rewind the tape. 按下这个按钮倒带。', '形容词: depressible 过去式: depressed 过去分词: depressed 现在分词: depressing 第三人称单数: depresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assembly', '[ə\'sembli]', 'n.集会；集合；议会；装配；与会者；聚集在一起的人；[计]汇编', '1. The assembly of students takes place in the auditorium. 学生们在大礼堂举行集会。 2. He rang the bell for school assembly. 他敲钟通知全校集合。 3. Each state had a governor and a state assembly. 每一州都有一个州长和州议会。 4. Jack was assigned to the assembly shop of the factory. 杰克被分配到厂里的装配间工作。', '名词复数: assemblies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('draft', '[dræft]', 'n.草稿；草图；汇票；征兵 vt.起草；征兵；选秀 adj.酝酿中的', '1. He drew a draft of the car. 他画了一张汽车的草图。 2. He has drawn up the design draft. 他拟订了设计草图。 3. He drew a draft on a pad then began his formal work. 他在便笺簿上画了草图，然后就开始正式工作了。 4. I propose issuing a time draft for US $ 100,000. 我建议开具价值10万美元的远期汇票。 5. Who will draft the indictment? 谁将起草起诉状？ 6. The Authority may suggest any other proposal it thinks fit for inclusion into the draft corporate plan. 市建局可提议其认为适合包括在事务计划草案内的任何其他提案。', '过去式: drafted 过去分词: drafted 现在分词: drafting 第三人称单数: drafts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ultimate', '[\'ʌltɪmət]', 'adj.根本的；极限的；最后的；终极的 n.终极；极品；根本', '1. Hard work is the ultimate source of success. 努力工作是成功之本。 2. This had been an ultimate issue. 这个问题是个原则性的问题。 3. GUPTA And the Ironman is the ultimate competition. 甘普塔铁人是一个极限的竞争。 4. I believe that I will bring my ultimate competitiveness in the advanced business management into full play with the guidance of professional teachers. 我认为在精英的师资力量的指导下我将在高级商业管理方面发挥我极限的竞争力。 5. Such behavior is the ultimate in idiocy. 这样的行为愚蠢透顶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abnormal', '[æb\'nɔːrml]', 'adj.反常的；不正常的；变态的 n.不正常的人', '1. We were very surprised at his abnormal behavior. 我们对他的反常行为感到非常吃惊。 2. At one time, she is fine, but at another, she is abnormal. 有时候，她表现得很好，有时候又失常。 3. He is mentally abnormal. 他精神不正常。 4. It\'s abnormal for the boy to eat so much. 这个孩子吃这么多是不正常的。 5. This is an abnormal phenomenon and we must work seriously to eradicate it. 这是一种很不正常的现象，一定要认真扭转。', '副词: abnormally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pending', '[\'pendɪŋ]', 'adj.待定的；即将发生或来临的 prep.直到；等待 ... 的时候；在 ... 期间', '1. The lawsuit was then pending. 那件讼案因而尚未解决。 2. A climax is pending. 高潮即将来到。 3. A decision on this matter is pending. 此事即将作出决定。 4. Series The command has been accepted, but the requested action is on hold, pending receipt of further information. 命令被接受,但是被要求的行动被保留,直到收到索取补充材料。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('facile', '[\'fæsl]', 'adj.易做到的；轻易完成的；麻利的', '1. The facile answer is a multimethod approach. 最方便的答案是多种方法的普查。 2. That is only a facile answer. 那只是一个很肤浅的回答。 3. What he said is a facile remark. 他说的话全是信口开河。 4. She is a facile speaker. 她是个能说会道的人。', '副词: facilely 名词: facileness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('level', '[\'levl]', 'n.数量；等级；水平；水平线 adj.平的；等高的 v.弄平；夷平；对准 adv.<废>水平地', '1. Levels of unemployment vary from region to region. 失业情形各地不同. 2. We each perceive the outside world differently according to our level. 我们每个人对外在世界的感觉,因个人等级不同而有所差异。 3. We must increase production levels. 我们必须提高生产水平。 4. The top of this mountain is three kilometers above the sea level. 这座山的山顶海拔三千米高。 5. A football field should be level. 足球场地应该平坦。 6. We need a mechanical digger to level the ground. 我们需要一台挖掘机来平整土地。', '副词: levelly 名词: levelness 过去式: leveled/levelled 过去分词: leveled/levelled 现在分词: leveling/levelling 第三人称单数: levels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reproach', '[rɪ\'proʊtʃ]', 'n.责备；耻辱 v.责备；申斥', '1. His reply sounded to me like a reproach. 他的回答在我听来象是责备。 2. Her behaviour was above/beyond reproach. 她的行为是无可指责的。 3. His reply sounded to her like a reproach. 他的回答在她听来像是责备。 4. A coward is a reproach to an army. 懦夫是军队的耻辱。 5. She reproached her husband for having forgotten their wedding anniversary. 她责怪丈夫忘了他们的结婚周年纪念日。', '形容词: reproachable 副词: reproachably 名词: reproachableness 过去式: reproached 过去分词: reproached 现在分词: reproaching 第三人称单数: reproaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pollinate', '[\'pɑːləneɪt]', 'v.给 ... 授粉', '1. Bees and butterflies pollinate the trees in the orchard. 蜜峰与蝴蝶将果园里的树授粉。 2. Many garden plants need butterflies to pollinate them. 许多园林植物需要蝴蝶授粉他们。', '名词: pollination');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('catholic', '[\'kæθlɪk]', 'adj.天主教的；(catholic)普遍的；广泛的 n.天主教徒', '1. Anselm\'s theology is not Catholic faith. 安塞姆的神学并不是天主教的信念。 2. The atom bomb is of catholic concern. 原子弹受到普遍的关注。 3. As a young person he had more catholic tastes than he does now. 他在年轻时兴趣比现在广泛得多。 4. Leonardo da Vinci was a catholic genius who excelled in almost everything he did. 达文西是一个广泛的天才,他做的很多事也得到成功。 5. He was a Catholic but didn\'t practise his religion. 他那时是天主教徒，但并不实践信仰。', '副词: catholically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impeach', '[ɪm\'piːtʃ]', 'v.归咎；怀疑；控告；弹劾', '1. Many people impeached the judge for taking bribes. 很多人控告法官受贿。 2. The Parliament decided to impeach the President. 国会决定弹劾总统。', '名词: impeacher 过去式: impeached 过去分词: impeached 现在分词: impeaching 第三人称单数: impeaches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kerosene', '[\'kerəsiːn]', 'n.煤油', '1. Soon there was a large demand for kerosene. 不久就产生了对煤油的大量需求。 2. It is like putting out a fire with kerosene. 这就像用煤油灭火。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('graphic', '[\'ɡræfɪk]', 'adj.生动的；图表的 n.图表', '1. The general gave a graphic account of the battle. 将军对战斗作了生动的描述。 2. He was a man of many words and many graphic gestures. 他是一个话多的人，还不停比划着生动的手势。 3. The newspaper article gave a graphic description of the earthquake. 报纸文章生动地描述了地震的情况。 4. The principal kept a graphic record of school attendance. 校长用图表记录学生的出席率。 5. Please help me to make a graphic. 请帮我做份图表。', '副词: graphically 名词: graphicness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('orientation', '[ˌɔːriən\'teɪʃn]', 'n.适应；定位；情况介绍；信仰；倾向；[计]定向；（学生）迎新会', '1. I needed some orientation at this stage. 我在这个阶段需要熟悉情况。 2. The arrangement must show a preferred orientation. 排列还必须呈现特定的指向。 3. The following action steps are a part of the foreman\'s orientation of the new worker. 以下内容是工头指导新工人时应采取的部分措施:介绍新的工作。 4. Christian Church that truly welcomes everybody disregarding your sexual orientation or denomination. 一个不论宗派及性取向，真正欢迎所有人的基督信仰教会。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('void', '[vɔɪd]', 'adj.空的；无效的；缺乏的 n.真空；空白；空虚 vt.使无效；排泄；使空出 vi.排泄', '1. Void function may not return a value 空函数不可返回一个值。 2. The court ruled that the claim was null and void. 法庭裁决此项要求无效。 3. His suggestions are totally void of common sense. 他的建议完全缺乏常识。 4. That part of the town is completely void of interest for visitors. 城镇的那部分对游客完全没有吸引力。 5. In the next weeks, government floated as in a void. 以后的几个星期,政府宛如漂浮于真空之中。 6. We will void the existing and issue a new one. 我们将把现有的作废，然后再出一张新的。', '名词: voider 过去式: voided 过去分词: voided 现在分词: voiding 第三人称单数: voids');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clamp', '[klæmp]', 'n.夹子；螺丝钳 vt.夹住；强加；压制', '1. The wood is held in position by a clamp. 木头用钳夹固定住了。 2. He used a clamp to hold the arm on the chair until the glue dried. 他用夹子将扶手夹在椅子上, 直到胶水干后再取下。 3. Try to clamp these two blocks of wood together. 试着把这两块木头夹在一起。 4. The wood is held in position by a clamp. 木头用钳夹固定住了。', '过去式: clamped 过去分词: clamped 现在分词: clamping 第三人称单数: clamps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('modeling', '[\'mɒdəlɪŋ]', 'n.造型；模特职业 动词model的现在分词.', '1. Form exploration in the clay modeling stage. 探索造型设计的油泥模型阶段。 2. Design rules and modeling method of helical intake ports are explored. 探讨了螺旋进气道的设计规律及造型的具体方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arable', '[\'ærəbl]', 'adj.可耕的；适合种植的 n.<英>可耕地', '1. Now in India, 63 percent of land is arable. 现在的印度，63%25的土地是可耕地。 2. Second,we have a large population but not enough arable land. 第二条是人口多，耕地少。 3. He farmed 200 acres of prime arable land. 他耕种了200英亩良田。 4. The soil proved too infertile to sustain real pasture or arable crops. 这土壤被证明太贫瘠,不能真正用作放牧或种植作物。', '名词: arability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('linguistic', '[lɪŋ\'ɡwɪstɪk]', 'adj.语言的；语言学的', '1. Gorbachev is a master of linguistic gestures. 戈尔巴乔夫精于语言的动作。 2. Thereafter, his linguistic abilities would decrease as he gets older. 年纪越大，掌握语言的能力相对的也越低。 3. She is pursuing her linguistic researches. 她在从事语言学的研究。 4. Viewed from the perspective of postcolonial translation studies, it is no more a purely aesthetic or linguistic act. 后殖民翻译研究视野中的翻译不再是纯美学的或纯语言学的行为。', '副词: linguistically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('turmoil', '[\'tɜːrmɔɪl]', 'n.混乱；骚动', '1. The London Stock Exchange is in turmoil today. 今天伦敦证券市场一片混乱。 2. I couldn\'t think; my mind was in a complete turmoil. 我无法思考，我的脑子里一片混乱。 3. In the turmoil resulting from the collision, the arrested man broke loose and ran off. 在撞车引起的一片混乱中，那个被捕的人挣脱逃走了。 4. The whole city was in a turmoil, and people came running from all directions. 全城骚动起来,人们从四面八方跑来了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('collaborate', '[kə\'læbəreɪt]', 'vi.合作；通敌', '1. She collaborated with her sister/She and her sister collaborated on a biography of their father. 她和姐姐合作写父亲的传记。 2. We would ask you to collaborate with us. 我们愿意请你们和我们合作。 3. This supplier and I collaborate on certain points. 我与供应商有数方面或以上的合作。', '形容词: collaborative 名词: collaboration 过去式: collaborated 过去分词: collaborated 现在分词: collaborating 第三人称单数: collaborates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crooked', '[\'krʊkɪd]', 'adj.弯曲的；歪的；不老实的；不正直的 动词crook的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He bent a crooked circle straight. 他把弯曲的铁丝弄直。 2. Don\'t take to crooked ways. 别走邪门歪道。 3. You can\'t trust John; he\'s cast in the same mould as his crooked father. 你不能相信约翰，他和他那不老实的父亲一模一样。 4. I won\'t play in their crooked poker games. 我不愿意参加他们那些骗人的扑克游戏。', '副词: crookedly 名词: crookedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genetically', '[dʒə\'netɪkli]', 'adv.遗传(基因)方面', '1. The sum of characteristics and associated potentialities transmitted genetically to an individual organism. 遗传而得的特征传给个体生物体的基因特征和相关潜力的总和', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exotic', '[ɪɡ\'zɑːtɪk]', 'adj.外来的；异国的；奇异的；脱衣舞的', '1. Exotic pets are the in thing right now. 外国宠物眼下很时髦。 2. The film retains much of the book\'s exotic flavour. 这部电影保存了原著的许多异国情调。 3. The taste of this exotic dish puts me off. 这道异国菜肴的味道令我望而却步。 4. The exotic atmosphere will fascinate you. 这里的异国情调风格将会把您深深地迷住。', '副词: exotically 名词: exoticness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rigid', '[\'rɪdʒɪd]', 'adj.坚硬的；严格的；固执的；僵硬的；刻板的', '1. The tent has a rigid support. 帐篷有一个坚硬的支柱。 2. He is a man of very rigid principles. 他是一个原则性很强的人。 3. He\'s very rigid in his ideas. 他的想法非常固执。 4. She was rigid with fear. 她害怕得全身僵住了。', '副词: rigidly 名词: rigidness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gradient', '[\'ɡreɪdiənt]', 'n.倾斜度；坡度；梯度', '1. It makes no odds because the gradient\'s still the same. 由于倾斜度没有变，所以没什么区别。 2. The car slid down the steep gradient into the river. 汽车滑下陡峭的斜坡掉入河中。 3. The road has a fairly steep gradient. 这条路的坡度相当陡峭。 4. The resulting solution is known as the gradient. 合成解就是通常的梯度风。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ascetic', '[ə\'setɪk]', 'adj.禁欲的 n.苦行者', '1. This is achieved by strict celibacy and ascetic practices. 这要通过严厉的独身生活和禁欲修行而达到。 2. Rabia went into the desert to pray and became an ascetic. 随后拉比尔走进沙漠祈祷，从此成为苦行者。', '副词: ascetically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('warrant', '[\'wɔːrənt]', 'n.委任状；凭证；根据；正当理由 vt.担保；保证；辩解；授权', '1. The police obtained a search warrant for his house. 警察拿到了搜查他家的搜查证。 2. Have you got a warrant of fitness for your car? 你有没有一张汽车合格证书? 3. You shouldn\'t arrest him without warrant. 你不能毫无根据地逮捕他。 4. He had no warrant for his suspicion. 他没有理由那么怀疑。 5. I will warrant him an honest and reliable man . 我担保他是个诚实可靠的人。', '形容词: warrantable 副词: warrantably 名词: warrantability 过去式: warranted 过去分词: warranted 现在分词: warranting 第三人称单数: warrants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('superintendent', '[ˌsuːpərɪn\'tendənt]', 'n.监督人；管理人；所长', '1. \"I hope he went fishing and comes back tomorrow, but I wouldn\'t bet my paycheck on it, \" said state police superintendent Clinton Pagano ... 州警察局长帕加诺说，\"我希望他钓鱼去了，明天就回来。但是我可不愿意拿我的薪水打赌(并无十分把握)。\"...', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conform', '[kən\'fɔːrm]', 'v.使一致；遵从', '1. His ideas do not conform to mine. 他的想法和我的不一致。 2. He doesn\'t conform to the usual stereotype of the city businessman with a dark suit and rolled umbrella. 他不像典型的城市商人那样，穿一身深色的套服、 带一把收好的雨伞。 3. She refused to conform to the normal social conventions. 她拒绝遵从正常的社会习俗。 4. She left home to escape the pressure to conform to her family\'s way of life. 她离家出走以求摆脱她家生活方式对她的束缚。', '名词: conformer 过去式: conformed 过去分词: conformed 现在分词: conforming 第三人称单数: conforms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hockey', '[\'hɑːki]', 'n.曲棍球', '1. Football and hockey players wear shoulder pads. 足球和曲棍球球员都戴垫肩。 2. I broke my foot while playing hockey. 在打曲棍球时我的脚骨折了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('copy', '[\'kɑːpi]', 'n.复制品；抄本；副本；一册；一份 v.复制；抄写；抄袭', '1. The painting is a copy of one in the museum. 这幅画是博物馆中的一幅画的复制品。 2. He asked his secretary to make a copy of the document. 他叫秘书把文件复制一份。 3. This copy does not correspond with the original. 这抄本与原件不符。 4. I managed to root out a copy of the document. 我好不容易才找到了文件的副本。 5. Would you copy this letter for me, please? 请为我复印一下这封信好吗？', '形容词: copyable 名词复数: copies 过去式: copied 过去分词: copied 现在分词: copying 第三人称单数: copies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('filthy', '[\'fɪlθi]', 'adj.污秽的；肮脏的；下流的；卑劣的', '1. The slum area was sordid and filthy beyond belief. 该贫民区之污秽肮脏简直令人难以置信。 2. He insulted others with filthy language. 他用污秽的语言侮辱人。 3. This side of the glass is filthy. 玻璃的这一面很脏。 4. The guy is always telling filthy jokes. 这家伙老是讲下流的笑话。', '副词: filthily 比较级: filthier 最高级: filthiest 名词: filthiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inclination', '[ˌɪnklɪ\'neɪʃn]', 'n.倾向；意愿；趋势；斜坡；倾斜度', '1. I have little inclination to listen to you all evening. 我可不愿意一晚上都听你说话。 2. She is not free to follow her own inclination in the matter ofmarriage. 她的婚姻不能自主。 3. You always follow your own inclination instead of thinking of our feelings. 你总是随心所欲而不考虑我们的情感。 4. Taking into account both of your inclination and our needs, the internship will be arranged in Fangben Shanghai Office or Suzhou Office. 实习地点将在综合考虑您的意愿及我们的需要后，安排在方本上海办公室或苏州办公室。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('receptacle', '[rɪ\'septəkl]', 'n.容器；花托；插座', '1. Please find me a receptacle for sugar. 请给我找一个放糖的容器。 2. Learning doesn\'t consist in being an empty receptacle. 学习并不是往空容器里塞东西。 3. Note: this kind of receptacle shell is Au-plated. 注:此类插座壳均为镀金。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consumer', '[kən\'sjuːmə]', 'n.消费者；用户；消费品', '1. We need more feedback from the consumer in order to improve our goods. 我们需要从消费者那里多得到些反馈信息以提高产品质量。 2. The price increases were passed on by the firm to the consumers. 那个公司把上涨的费用都转嫁到了消费者身上。 3. We should adopt the consumers\' suggestion. 我们应该接受用户的建议。 4. Consumer goods production was to go up by 6.6 percent in that city. 在那个城市消费品生产将增长6.6%25。', '名词: consumership');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hollow', '[\'hɑːloʊ]', 'adj.空的；空洞的；凹陷的；虚伪的；(声音)沉闷的 n.山谷；洞；窟窿 vt.挖空 vi.形成空洞 adv.完全地；彻底', '1. This tree looks high and strong but actually its trunk is hollow. 这棵树看起来又高又壮，实际上树干是空的。 2. His protests on human rights sound hollow. 他就人权问题提出的抗议听来很空洞。 3. He was thin and his cheeks were hollow. 他很瘦,连面颊都凹陷了下去。 4. An open enemy is better than a hollow friend. 宁有公开的敌人，不要虚伪的朋友。 5. The track dipped, weaving into a wooded hollow. 小路消失了，迂回前行到了一片多树的山谷里。 6. The Indians used to hollow out a log to make a canoe. 印第安人过去常挖空圆木制成独木舟。 7. I played Max at chess yesterday and beat him hollow. 昨天我跟麦克斯下棋，杀得他一败涂地。', '副词: hollowly 比较级: hollower 最高级: hollowest 名词: hollowness 过去式: hollowed 过去分词: hollowed 现在分词: hollowing 第三人称单数: hollows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adept', '[ə\'dept]', 'adj.熟练的；老练的 n.名手；专家', '1. He was astonishingly adept at manipulating the big machine. 他操作这台大机器熟练得惊人。 2. Like any culturally adept traveler, the tribe has changed its appearance throughout its history. 就像任何聪明熟练的旅行老鸟，从历史上到如今这个部族一直不断地改变自己的面貌。 3. It may not have the best table manners, but this strange looking creature is certainly a very adept and unusual percussionist, which should help provide Nick with a good beat. 也许它的吃相并不雅观，但这种相貌奇特的动物肯定是一位老练的打击乐高手，能为尼克提供一些不错的素材。 4. Many became adept, and thousands of fires were extinguished before they took hold. 其中有很多人成了专家，几千颗烧夷弹还没有燃烧，火势头就被扑灭了。', '副词: adeptly 名词: adeptness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emaciated', '[ɪ\'meɪʃieɪtɪd]', 'adj.瘦弱的；憔悴的 动词emaciate的过去式和过去分词.', '1. How to make an emaciated person become more healthy? 怎么才能使一个瘦弱的人变得健康些？ 2. Obturator hernia is rare.It often occurs in elderly, emaciated women. 闭孔疝并不常见,主要发生在年纪大且身体瘦弱的女性身上。 3. In the light of a single candle, she can see his emaciated face. 透过一根蜡烛,她能看到他憔悴的面孔。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perfume', '[pər\'fjuːm]', 'n.香水；香气 vt.洒香水于；使香气弥漫', '1. The room reeked of cheap perfume. 房间里弥漫著劣质香水的呛鼻气味。 2. The smell of her perfume lingered in the empty house. 空屋里仍然飘溢著她的香水味。 3. A mist of perfume hung in the air. 空气中飘溢著香水的雾气。 4. Can you smell the perfume of the roses? 你能闻到玫瑰花的香味吗？ 5. She perfumed herself with Eau de Cologne. 她身上洒著古龙水。', '过去式: perfumed 过去分词: perfumed 现在分词: perfuming 第三人称单数: perfumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strategy', '[\'strætədʒi]', 'n.策略；战略', '1. The strategy was designed to wear down the enemy\'s resistance. 这一策略旨在逐步削弱敌人的抵抗力。 2. We will discuss our sale strategy this year. 我们将讨论有关今年销售策略的问题。 3. He is an expert in military strategy. 他是军事战略专家。 4. Each country needs to forge its own industrial development strategy. 每个国家都需要制定自己的工业发展战略。', '名词复数: strategies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extraordinary', '[ɪk\'strɔːrdəneri]', 'adj.非凡的；特别的；特派的', '1. He has an extraordinary memory. 他有非凡的记忆力。 2. His extraordinary skill was praised by all. 他超凡的技艺博得了广泛的赞誉。 3. I find it very extraordinary. 我觉得这非常离奇。 4. He is full of extraordinary ideas. 他满脑子都是离奇的想法。', '副词: extraordinarily');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fashionable', '[\'fæʃnəbl]', 'adj.流行的；时髦的', '1. We have some fashionable patterns here. 我们这儿有些流行的款式。 2. She likes to wear fashionable clothes. 她喜欢穿流行的衣服。 3. These fashionable jackets are rather expensive. 这些时髦的夹克衫相当贵。 4. It was performed in fashionable Casino ballrooms. 人们在时髦的娱乐舞厅里跳这种舞蹈。', '副词: fashionably 名词: fashionability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emerge', '[i\'mɜːrdʒ]', 'vi.浮现；(由某种状态)脱出；(事实)显现出来', '1. A wonderful idea emerged in my mind. 我的脑海里浮现出一个极妙的想法。 2. Man has gradually emerged from barbarism into civilization over the long history. 在悠久的历史长河中人类逐渐脱离野蛮状态而进入文明。 3. Many facts emerged as a result of the investigation. 调查结果,许多事实暴露出来。', '过去式: emerged 过去分词: emerged 现在分词: emerging 第三人称单数: emerges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cylinder', '[\'sɪlɪndər]', 'n.圆筒；汽缸；圆柱体', '1. The cylinder is a crucial part of the washing machine. 滚筒是洗衣机必不可少的部分。 2. She handed over a small metal cylinder. 她递过来一个小的金属圆筒。 3. The engine is misfiring badly on one cylinder. 发动机有一个汽缸严重失灵。 4. The accident didn\'t do much damage to the cylinder. 在意外事故中，汽缸没有受到重大损坏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unity', '[\'juːnəti]', 'n.整体；统一；一致；结合', '1. These works, taken together, are essentially a unity. 这些作品，放在一起，基本上是一个整体。 2. The figure on the left spoils the unity of the painting. 左边的人物有损于画面的整体性。 3. He made a speech about the need for unity. 他发表了有关统一之必要的演讲。 4. They maintained only formal unity among themselves. 他们只在表面上保持一致。', '名词复数: unities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('queer', '[kwɪr]', 'adj.古怪的；奇怪的；可疑的；<俚>同性恋的 n.<俚>同性恋者 vt.把...弄糟；使陷入不利', '1. There is something queer about him. 他有些古怪。 2. Her queer way of dressing attracted the attention of the passerby. 她古怪的着装方式引起了过路人的注意。 3. I have a queer dream last night. 我昨晚做了一个奇怪的梦。 4. I heard some very queer noises in the garden. 我听到花园里有些可疑的声音。 5. His blunder would certainly queer his chances of promotion. 他犯的大错肯定会毁了他晋升的机会。', '形容词: queerish 副词: queerly 比较级: queerer 最高级: queerest 名词: queerness 过去式: queered 过去分词: queered 现在分词: queering 第三人称单数: queers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('neglect', '[nɪ\'ɡlekt]', 'vt.忽略；忽视；疏忽 n.疏忽；忽视', '1. You shouldn\'t neglect your health. 你不该忽略你的健康。 2. No country can afford to neglect education. 任何国家都不容忽视教育。 3. He neglected to write and say \"Thank you\". 他忘了写信道谢。 4. She was severely criticized for neglect of duty. 她因玩忽职守而受到严厉批评。', '名词: neglecter 过去式: neglected 过去分词: neglected 现在分词: neglecting 第三人称单数: neglects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vindicate', '[\'vɪndɪkeɪt]', 'v.证明无辜；证明 ... 正确；维护（权利等）；<废>报仇', '1. I consider that I\'ve been completely vindicated. 我认为已经证实了我完全无辜。 2. The report of the committee vindicated him. 委员会的报告说明他是清白的。 3. The report fully vindicated the unions. 这份报告充分说明工会是正确的。 4. He tried hard to vindicate his honor. 他拼命维护自己的名誉。', '名词: vindicator 过去式: vindicated 过去分词: vindicated 现在分词: vindicating 第三人称单数: vindicates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('credit', '[\'kredɪt]', 'n.信用；荣誉；学分；赞扬；贷款；赊欠；贷方；存款 (复)credits: 演职员名单. v.归功于；相信；记入贷方', '1. Credit counseling helped us get out from under. 信用咨询使我们免除了忧虑 2. Where can I see my credit score? 我在哪能看到我的信用分数? 3. They are working hard for the credit of China. 他们在为中国的荣誉而努力工作。 4. You must pass the examination to get credit for the course. 你必须通过考试才能获得那门课程的学分。 5. At the time, we used to credit everything to one person. 那时大家把什么都归功于一个人。', '过去式: credited 过去分词: credited 现在分词: crediting 第三人称单数: credits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('harness', '[\'hɑːrnɪs]', 'n.马具；安全带；甲胄；系在身上的绳子 vt.束以马具；披上甲胄；利用；管理；控制', '1. Stirrup is an important part of harness. 马镫是马具的一个重要的部分。 2. You can not judge of the horse by the harness. 凭马具难断马优劣。 3. Safety harness is quite necessary in terms of the accidents. 考虑到意外事故,安全带是必要的。 4. The parachutist was buckled into his harness. 跳伞者扣上了背带。 5. I harness the horse to the cart. 我把马套在车上。', '名词: harnesser 过去式: harnessed 过去分词: harnessed 现在分词: harnessing 第三人称单数: harnesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('daze', '[deɪz]', 'vt. 使 ... 茫然； 使 ... 眩目 n. 恍惚； 晕眩', '1. We drove home in an absolute daze. 我们茫然一片地驱车回家。 2. I\'ve been in a complete daze since hearing the news. 自从听到那消息，我一直茫然不知所措。 3. He had been in a daze all the way to New York. 他去纽约途中一路恍惚。', '过去式: dazed 过去分词: dazed 现在分词: dazing 第三人称单数: dazes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('facial', '[\'feɪʃl]', 'adj.脸部的；面部的 n.美容', '1. She is having a facial massage. 她正做脸部按摩。 2. The cream dissolves facial hair. 这种化妆品能清除脸上的汗毛。 3. She wiped off the sweat from her face with a piece of facial tissue. 她用一张面巾纸擦掉脸上的汗水。 4. The scientists are studying facial proportions. 科学家们正在研究面部比例。 5. She had a facial at the beauty parlor. 她在美容院做了一次美容。', '副词: facially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strengthen', '[\'streŋθn]', 'v.加强；变坚固', '1. He has been brought in to strengthen the defence. 已请他来加强后卫力量。 2. We will strengthen the protection of wet land. 我们将加强湿地保护。 3. Every effort was made to strengthen unity. 大家尽力加强团结。 4. The current strengthened as we moved down the river. 我们顺流而下时，水流更急了。', '名词: strengthener 过去式: strengthened 过去分词: strengthened 现在分词: strengthening 第三人称单数: strengthens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rub', '[rʌb]', 'v.擦；摩擦；搓；惹恼 n.困难；障碍；擦', '1. I rubbed the window with a cloth. 我用一块布擦窗子。 2. We may have to rub polish on the floor. 我们可能得在地板上涂上光剂了。 3. He asked me to rub up the silver. 他让我把银器擦一擦。 4. The wheel\'s rubbing on the mudguard. 车轮蹭著了挡泥板。 5. We need money badly, but there\'s the rub: no one will lend us any. 我们急需要钱,但困难的是:谁也不会借钱给我们。', '过去式: rubbed 过去分词: rubbed 现在分词: rubbing 第三人称单数: rubs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accusation', '[ˌækju\'zeɪʃn]', 'n.控告；指控；非难', '1. His father was under an accusation then. 他父亲当时受到控告。 2. The accusation was that he had murdered a man. 他被控告杀了人。 3. It was frivolous of him to make such an accusation. 他提出这样的指控真无聊。 4. The accusation that I stole the money is false. 说我偷了钱的指控是不实的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('statistics', '[stə\'tɪstɪks]', 'n.统计学；统计；统计数字', '1. He is a professor of statistics. 他教授统计学。 2. There is a compulsory course in statistics. 有一门统计学的必修课。 3. Get me a printout of the statistics. 给我一份打印出的统计资料。 4. He is taking statistics. 他正在进行统计。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imminent', '[\'ɪmɪnənt]', 'adj.逼近的；即将发生的', '1. He was faced with imminent death. 他面临逼近的死亡。 2. They are unaware of imminent danger. 他们没意识到逼近的危险。 3. Rumours of an imminent earthquake startled a panic. 谣传即将发生地震引起了一阵恐慌。 4. The black clounds show that a storm is imminent. 乌云预示暴风雨即将来临。', '副词: imminently 名词: imminentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bewilder', '[bɪ\'wɪldər]', 'vt. 使迷惑； 使 ... 不知所措', '1. You bewildered me. 你把我搞糊涂了。 2. Big city traffic bewilders me. 大城市的交通使我晕头转向。', '副词: bewilderedly 名词: bewilderedness 过去式: bewildered 过去分词: bewildered 现在分词: bewildering 第三人称单数: bewilders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('herd', '[hɜːrd]', 'n.兽群；牧人；群 vt.放牧；群集；使 ... 成群，把…赶到一起 vi.聚在一起', '1. A large herd could wreck a train. 庞大的兽群将会使火车失事。 2. The report of the gun will scare the herd. 枪声会惊吓兽群。 3. The herdsman looks after a herd of animals. 牧人放牧着一群牲畜。 4. The Goatherd scolded them for their ingratitude in leaving him, when during the storm he had taken more care of them than of his own herd. 牧人骂他们忘恩负义说他曾经在风雪中对他们照顾得比自己的羊还好。 5. Dogs are often trained to herd sheep. 狗常被训练来放羊。 6. You should not herd with the man as him. 你不应和他那样的人来往。', '过去式: herded 过去分词: herded 现在分词: herding 第三人称单数: herds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('electricity', '[ɪˌlek\'trɪsəti]', 'n.电；电学；电流；热情', '1. The electricity failure paralyzed the water supply. 停电使水供应陷于瘫痪。 2. The interruption of electricity made us unable to do anything. 电力的中断让我们什么也不能做。 3. While I was cooking supper the electricity went off. 我正在做晚饭时停电了。 4. Both students have made quite a few experiments on electricity. 这两个学生都做了不少电学实验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('retard', '[\'riːtɑːrd]', 'vt.妨碍；迟延；拖住 vi.受到延迟 n.阻止；迟延；减速', '1. Cold weather retards the growth of the crops. 寒冷的天气妨碍了庄稼生长。 2. Lack of science and education retards social progress. 缺乏科学和教育会妨碍社会进步。 3. They also used it for sunburns and to retard the aging process. 他们还用它来防治日光灼伤，以及延缓衰老过程。 4. The heavy rain retarded our arrival by seventy minutes. 大雨使我们推迟了七十分钟才到达。 5. The rearward regiments are in painful retard. 后续部队受到令人难以忍受的阻碍。', '名词: retarder 过去式: retarded 过去分词: retarded 现在分词: retarding 第三人称单数: retards');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('veteran', '[\'vetərən]', 'adj.老练的 n.老手；老兵', '1. A good idea soaked into that veteran worker. 那位老工人的头脑里有了一个好主意。 2. This veteran cadre is looked up to by everybody. 这位老干部受到众人的尊敬。 3. The baseball veteran loved to coach young players. 这位棒球老手喜欢指导年轻选手。 4. That comrade writing these poems is a veteran. 写这些诗的那个同志是个老兵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('certificate', '[sər\'tɪfɪkət]', 'n.执照；证(明)书 vt.认可；批准；发证书给 ...', '1. The driver\'s certificate was suspended by the police. 这个司机的驾驶执照被警察吊销了。 2. He was afforded a certificate upon completion of his course of study. 他结业时被授予证书。 3. This is an accredited course and participants will receive 4.5 college credits and a world recognized Certificate of Nutrition upon completion. 本课程设学分制，完成课程的直销商可获国际认可大学学分，结业时将获颁发盖有美国大溪谷州立大学盖印的营养证书。 4. Bocog originally promised to issue a certificate of recognition to the participant in its global campaign whose slogan was adopted. 北京奥组委最初承诺，在全球征集活动中，一旦某一口号获选，将向口号的提出者颁发认可证书。', '形容词: certificatory 过去式: certificated 过去分词: certificated 现在分词: certificating 第三人称单数: certificates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vapor', '[\'veɪpə]', 'n.蒸汽；水蒸汽 v.蒸发；汽化', '1. The locomotive vomits out vapor when getting started. 火车头启动时喷出大量蒸汽。 2. A cloud is a mass of vapor in the sky. 云是天空中的水汽团。 3. Warm air can contain more water vapor than cold air. 热空气要较冷空气容纳更多的水蒸汽。 4. Topically, 1 pound of steam can be used to generate a little less than 1 pound of vapor through evaporation. 总体来说一磅的水通过蒸发可以产生不到一磅的蒸汽。', '名词: vaporer 过去式: vapored 过去分词: vapored 现在分词: vaporing 第三人称单数: vapors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affect', '[ə\'fekt]', 'vt.影响；感动；作用', '1. How does interest rate affect the price of bonds? 利率如何影响债券的价格? 2. She was deeply affected by the sad story. 她深深被那个悲伤的故事感动了。 3. His charm doesn\'t affect or impress me. 他的魅力对我不起作用.', '名词: affecter 过去式: affected 过去分词: affected 现在分词: affecting 第三人称单数: affects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('demise', '[dɪ\'maɪz]', 'n.死亡；转让房产；让位 v.让渡；遗赠；转让；死亡', '1. This loss led to the demise of the business. 这一损失导致了公司的倒闭。 2. Upon his demise his house passed to his son. 他故世后，房子便传给了儿子。 3. The demise of the old man\'s property cause much dispute upon his death. 老人死时，财产的让渡问题引起许多争执。', '形容词: demisable 过去式: demised 过去分词: demised 现在分词: demising 第三人称单数: demises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('precursor', '[priː\'kɜːrsər]', 'n.先驱；前任；前兆；[生物]前体，前驱体', '1. The precursor of the modern car was a horseless carriage with a petrol engine. 现代汽车的前身是不用马拉的，装有汽油发动机的车子。 2. Her precursor as school principal was an eminent educator. 她任校长前是一位卓越的教育家。 3. Opposition by colonists to unfair taxation by the British was a precursor of the Revolution. 殖民地居民对英国不公正税收的反抗预示着革命的到来。 4. Lysine is a precursor of certain alkaloids. 赖氨酸是某些生物碱的前体。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forte', '[fɔːrt]', 'n.[C, sing]长处；特长；优点；[音乐]强音记号', '1. Singing is not really my forte, but I\'ll try. 唱歌实在不是我擅长的，但是我试着唱唱看。 2. Diplomacy was not Margaret\'s forte . 玛格丽特对外交事务不内行。 3. His forte is after-dinner speeches. 他的特长是饭后演说。 4. To negotiate with our buyers is my forte. 与买方谈判是我的特长。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('original', '[ə\'rɪdʒənl]', 'adj.原始的；最初的；有独创性的；原版的 n.原版；真品；怪人；有独创性的人 n.起源', '1. Our original plan was to go to Spain, but it was too expensive. 我们的原始计划是去西班牙,但是去那里太贵了。 2. I prefer your original plan to these. 我认为你最初的计划比这些都要好。 3. His designs are highly original. 他的设计独树一帜。 4. This is the original painting, and the others are copies. 这画是原作,其他的是复制品。 5. The Greek translation is faithful to the Hebrew original. 希腊语翻译很忠实于希伯来原文。 6. Fujian Province is the original and major production region of jasmine tea. 福建省是茉莉花茶的起源地和主产区。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interior', '[ɪn\'tɪriər]', 'adj.内地的；国内的；内部的 n.内部；内在', '1. The people of the African interior began to offer gold in exchange for the goods they needed from abroad. 从此后非洲内地的各族人民开始用黄金交换他们所需要的外国货物。 2. Despite this, at the Siberian station stops, the still heat of the Russian interior burned the skin within seconds and the silence echoed. 尽管如此，在西伯利亚车站停车的时候，瞬间就能感受到俄罗斯内地的炎热烧灼皮肤，沉寂的大地也有了回声。 3. They are engaged in interior trade. 他们从事国内贸易。 4. We are fascinated by the delicate interior design of the apartment. 我们被这所公寓的精致的室内装潢设计吸引。 5. Xi\'an is a city in the interior of China. 西安是一个内陆城市。', '副词: interiorly 名词: interiority');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('choir', '[\'kwaɪər]', 'n.唱诗班；合唱队；唱诗班的席位', '1. The choir sang the 23rd Psalm. 唱诗班唱《旧约·诗篇》之第23篇。 2. The choir sang the amens beautifully. 唱诗班唱的阿门非常优美。 3. The choir sang sweetly, and none more so than the Welsh boy. 唱诗班唱得很悦耳，尤其是没人比得上那个威尔士男孩儿。 4. The choir was singing distinctly out of tune in places. 合唱团有些地方明显唱走调了。', '过去式: choired 过去分词: choired 现在分词: choiring 第三人称单数: choirs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('satiate', '[\'seɪʃieɪt]', 'v.使饱足；使厌腻；充分满足 adj.饱足的；厌腻的', '1. She pushed her chair back from the table,satiated. 她把椅子从餐桌处向後挪了挪 2. He was satiated with pleasure. 他厌倦了享乐。 3. People\'s government should satiate the people\'s needs. 人民政府应充分满足人民的需要。', '名词: satiation 过去式: satiated 过去分词: satiated 现在分词: satiating 第三人称单数: satiates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gleam', '[ɡliːm]', 'v.闪烁；隐约地闪现 n.微光；闪光；闪现', '1. The lighthouse of the island gleamed in the distance. 远处岛上的灯塔在闪耀着。 2. His face gleamed with pleasure. 他的脸上闪现出欢快的神色。 3. I could see the faint gleam of light in the distance. 我能看见远处微弱的灯光。 4. I saw the gleam of the knife as it flashed through the air. 我看见了刀在空中划过时的闪光。', '名词: gleamer 过去式: gleamed 过去分词: gleamed 现在分词: gleaming 第三人称单数: gleams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adjunct', '[\'ædʒʌŋkt]', 'n.附属物；附件；修饰语', '1. Are social mission and business activities being mixed in an existing organization as an adjunct to existing profit or social mission goals? 社会使命和商务活动时候是作为现有利润或社会使命目标的附属物而溶入到现有组织的？ 2. When disease is seen as an invader, forced upon the integrity of the self for no reason, then the individual seems powerless and the conscious mind an adjunct. 当疾病被视作侵略者，无缘无故地强加在自我的完整性上时，个人就变得软弱无力，意识头脑也成了附属物。 3. The word is an adjunct of that verb. 这个词是那个动词的修饰语。', '形容词: adjunctive 名词: adjunction');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rap', '[ræp]', 'n.轻敲；拍击；责骂；厉声说出；说唱音乐；谈话；最少量 vi.轻敲；表演说唱音乐；畅谈', '1. There is a light rap at the door. 有轻轻的敲门声。 2. He took a bad rap on the head when he fell. 他跌倒时头被猛撞了一下。 3. Louise got a bum rap for taking sides with Richard. 路易斯因为偏袒理查德而受到责骂。 4. The bank clerk got a rap on the knuckles for his carelessness. 那个银行职员因为粗心大意而受到责骂。 5. The chairman rapped on the table for order. 主席敲击桌子以维持秩序。', '过去式: rapped 过去分词: rapped 现在分词: rapping 第三人称单数: raps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subjection', '[səb\'dʒekʃn]', 'n.征服；服从；隶属', '1. The country\'s subjection of its neighbor has been finished. 该国对邻国的征服已经完成。 2. The subjection of the rebels took a long time. 征服这些造反派花了很长时间。 3. She inherits her mother\'s talents, and must have been under subjection to her. 由于她继承了母亲的天赋,必须服从于她。 4. The nation was kept in subjection. 这个民族已经沦为附庸。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('undaunted', '[ˌʌn\'dɔːntɪd]', 'adj.不屈不挠的；无畏的', '1. We should learn from her undaunted spirits. 我们应该学习她那种不屈不挠的精神。 2. He continued the climb, undaunted by his fall. 他跌下来也并未气馁，继续攀登。 3. It was undaunted of him to go there alone. 他一个人去，真是勇敢。 4. But it\'s not a problem for such an undaunted person like me. 但对我这样一个现在大无畏的人来说，这并不是大问题。', '副词: undauntedly 名词: undauntedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swarm', '[swɔːrm]', 'n.群；蜂群 v.云集；充满', '1. I saw a swarm of bees attacking the poor monkey. 我看到一群蜜蜂正在攻击可怜的猴子。 2. He has received a swarm of letters. 他已经收到了一大批信件。 3. The locust swarm has destroyed all the crops and vegetables. 蝗虫群毁坏了所有的庄稼和蔬菜。 4. Like bees in a swarm, these stars move on ever changing orbits. 好比蜂群内的蜜蜂那般，球状星团内的恒星运行在不断变化的轨道之上。 5. Many students swarm into the canteen after class. 放学后,很多学生拥进食堂。', '名词: swarmer 过去式: swarmed 过去分词: swarmed 现在分词: swarming 第三人称单数: swarms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deficient', '[dɪ\'fɪʃnt]', 'adj.不足的；不充分的；有缺陷的', '1. We are deficient in hands. 我们人手不够。 2. The crops are suffering from deficient rain. 庄稼因雨量不足而遭受损害。 3. Our knowledge of the matter is deficient. 我们对此事了解不足。 4. A mentally deficient person is one who is weak-minded. 一个智力上不足的人是个低能的人。', '副词: deficiently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fluffy', '[\'flʌfi]', 'adj.毛绒绒的；蓬松的；空洞的', '1. He found that fluffy puppy on the street. 他在路上捡来那只毛绒绒的小狗。 2. Dasey also was wearing fluffy pink slippers that Frank had given her. 德茜也喜欢穿毛绒绒的粉红色拖鞋，那是福兰克送给她的。 3. A fluffy gray mantle and patches of tall grass help a cub hide on the open savanna. 在辽阔开放的热带草原上，小猎豹可以凭借身上蓬松的灰色毛皮隐藏在长长的草丛中。 4. In this beautiful head study, you can easily see the exaggerated feathering that forms the fluffy coat. 你可以容易看出夸张的羽毛似的蓬松的毛发。', '副词: fluffily 比较级: fluffier 最高级: fluffiest 名词: fluffiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attendance', '[ə\'tendəns]', 'n.出席；出席人数；出席率', '1. My attendance at school is excellent. 我在学校的出席情况极好。 2. Attendance at the meeting is mandatory. 出席会议是必要的 3. The number of the attendance will run to eighty. 这些出席人数约有八十名。 4. The attendance was encouragingly high. 出席人数之多令人振奋。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tarnish', '[\'tɑːrnɪʃ]', 'n.晦暗；污渍 v.沾污', '1. Moisture leads to the tarnish of the silverware. 湿气使得银器毫无光泽。 2. Check cutlery to make sure them free from tarnish and stain. 检查餐具的清洁,保证光亮无污渍。 3. The firm\'s good name was badly tarnished by the scandal. 这件丑事玷污了公司的好名声。 4. If news of this gets out, it will tarnish his image. 如果这消息传出去', '形容词: tarnishable 过去式: tarnished 过去分词: tarnished 现在分词: tarnishing 第三人称单数: tarnishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amazed', '[ə\'meɪzd]', 'adj.吃惊的；惊愕的 动词amaze的过去式和过去分词.', '1. I was amazed to see how readily I understood. 令我吃惊的是，我竟理解得这么透彻。 2. Virtually everyone is amazed and wants the technology in their home. 事实上每个人是吃惊的并且在他们的家中想要技术。 3. Who enraged almost as much as he amazed him. 使他既愤慨又惊愕的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('methodical', '[mə\'θɑːdɪkl]', 'adj.有条不紊的；井然的', '1. A scientist is usually a methodical person. 科学家通常是办事有条不紊的人。 2. This book is about systematic and methodical training. 这本书是关于有系统和有规律的训练。', '副词: methodically 异体字: methodic 名词: methodicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('millennium', '[mɪ\'leniəm]', 'n.一千年；太平盛世', '1. The current hypothesis is that the Vedic form of Sanskrit survived until the middle of the first millennium BC. 当前的假说就是梵语形式的吠陀经保存了下来，直到公元前一千年中叶为止。 2. Each of these Pyramid inches represents one millennium, or 1000 years, showing that Zoroaster was the middle Manifestation. 每一个这些棱椎的每一英寸都代表一个千禧年，或一千年，表明琐罗亚斯德是中间的表现。 3. I do not expect the millennium to come during my lifetime. 我并不指望我这一生中能碰上太平盛世。', '形容词: millennial 副词: millennially 名词: millennialism 名词复数: millenniums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acrimony', '[ækrɪmoʊni]', 'n.(语言；态度等)刻薄；辛辣', '1. This book review was written with acrimony. 这篇书评语调刻薄。 2. The acrimony of his remarks alienated his audience. 他说话尖刻, 这使观众和他疏远了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affable', '[\'æfəbl]', 'adj.谦恭有礼的；和蔼可亲的；易于交谈的；慈祥的；殷勤的', '1. I am affable to everyone. 我对每个人都彬彬有礼。 2. We all like this affable teacher. 我们都喜欢这位和蔼可亲的老师。 3. He found her parents very affable. 他觉得她父母很好说话。 4. Granny smiled an affable smile. 奶奶慈祥地笑了笑。', '副词: affably 名词: affability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('negative', '[\'neɡətɪv]', 'adj.否定的；消极的；负面的；负的 n.否定；反面意见；底片；[数]负数 vt.否定', '1. Now I am afraid of getting a negative response. 现在真害怕收到否定的答复。 2. You can\'t learn anything with negative attitude. 你用消极的态度什么也学不到。 3. He conducted a negative campaign against his opponent. 他对他的对手进行了负面打击。 4. This negative pressure phase is of short duration. 负压周期的延续时间很短。 5. The answer to my request was in the negative. 对我的请求的答复是否定的。 6. The government negatived our request for financing. 政府否决了我们融资的请求。', '副词: negatively 名词: negativeness 过去式: negatived 过去分词: negatived 现在分词: negativing 第三人称单数: negatives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('baby-sit', '[\'beɪbɪˌsɪt]', 'v.(代人临时)照看小孩；当临时保姆', '1. You are not expected to baby - sit this evening. 你今晚不需要当临时保姆。', '过去式: baby-sat 过去分词: baby-sat 现在分词: baby-sitting 第三人称单数: baby-sits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('toe', '[toʊ]', 'n.脚趾；足尖 vt.趾触；趾踢 vi.踮着脚尖走 abbr.吨油当量（=Ton Oil Equivalent）', '1. Each foot has five toes. 每只脚有五个脚趾头。 2. He stepped on my toes. 他踩着了我的脚趾头。 3. I\'ve stubbed my toe on a rock. 我的脚趾碰到石头上了。 4. My boot is pressing against a blister on my toe. 我的靴子挤压了我脚趾上的水泡。 5. He toed the cigarette out. 他将香烟踩灭。 6. He toes out. 他踮着脚走了出去。', '过去式: toed 过去分词: toed 现在分词: toeing 第三人称单数: toes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assuage', '[ə\'sweɪdʒ]', 'v.缓和；减轻；镇定', '1. Nothing can assuage the widow\'s grief. 什么也不能缓和这寡妇的哀伤。 2. His reply did little to assuage my suspicions. 他的答覆一点也没有减少我的怀疑。', '名词: assuagement 过去式: assuaged 过去分词: assuaged 现在分词: assuaging 第三人称单数: assuages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('larva', '[\'lɑːrvə]', 'n.幼虫；幼体', '1. The larva hatches out and lives in the soil. 幼虫孵化之后就在土壤里生活。 2. It shows the metamorphosis of a larva into a butterfly. 它展示了从幼虫变成蝴蝶的过程。 3. The tadpole is the larva of the frog. 蝌蚪是青蛙的幼体。 4. A caterpillar is the larva of a butterfly. 毛虫是蝴蝶的幼体。', '形容词: larval 名词复数: larvae');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bicker', '[\'bɪkər]', 'v.斗嘴；闪烁；发出潺潺声 n.口角；潺潺流水声', '1. They always bicker when they meet at school. 在学校见面时他们总是争吵。 2. The two children used to bicker about who should do the washing-up. 这两个小孩子过去常为该由谁洗餐具一事而争吵。 3. This sort of discussion seemed only to cause bicker. 这一类讨论似乎只会导致口角。', '名词: bickerer 过去式: bickered 过去分词: bickered 现在分词: bickering 第三人称单数: bickers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appeal', '[ə\'piːl]', 'n.恳求；呼吁；上诉；吸引力 n.(体育比赛中)诉请裁决 v.呼吁；有吸引力；求助；诉请', '1. Their appeal for help went unheeded. 他们求助的呼吁未受到注意。 2. He made one last appeal to his father to forgive him. 他最後一次恳求父亲宽恕他。 3. His appeal to a higher court was set aside. 他的上诉被驳回。 4. The judge rejected the appeal made by the prisoner for a new trial. 法官驳回了犯人提出重新审理的上诉。 5. The police appealed to the crowd not to panic. 警方向群众呼吁不要惊慌。', '形容词: appealable 名词: appealability 过去式: appealed 过去分词: appealed 现在分词: appealing 第三人称单数: appeals');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('displace', '[dɪs\'pleɪs]', 'v.取代；移置；替换', '1. Weeds tend to displace other plants. 杂草越来越多，有取代其他植物之势。 2. Moderates have displaced the extremists on the committee. 在委员会中，稳健派人士取代了激进派人士。 3. Please don\'t displace my dictionaries. 请别动我的词典。 4. The indigenous population was soon displaced by the settlers. 没过多久，外来移民就把当地人赶出了家园。', '形容词: displaceable 名词: displacer 过去式: displaced 过去分词: displaced 现在分词: displacing 第三人称单数: displaces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('virtually', '[\'vɜːrtʃuəli]', 'adv.实际上；几乎', '1. It is virtually impossible to predict the future accurately. 精确预言未来的事实际上是办不到的。 2. It\'s not an agreement as such, but it will have virtually the same effect as one. 它算不上是协定, 但实际上起协定的作用。 3. This opinion was held by virtually all the experts. 差不多所有的专家都持这一看法。 4. Virtually all the members were in agreement with the proposal. 几乎所有的成员都同意这项提议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('staple', '[\'steɪpl]', 'n.U形(订书)钉；主要产物(要素)；原料(地) adj.主要的；重要的 vt.用订书机装订', '1. He used a pair of scissors to take the staple out of the document. 他用剪刀将订书钉从文件上取了出来。 2. Coffee is the staple of this district. 咖啡是这个地区的主要产品。 3. Bread, potato and other staple continue to rise in price. 面包、土豆及其他主食的价格继续上涨。 4. For example, rice is a staple crop in much of Asia. 例如，在亚洲大米是原料农作物。 5. Short stories are her staple reading. 短篇小说是她经常看的读物。 6. He stapled the paper together. 他把文件钉在一起。', '过去式: stapled 过去分词: stapled 现在分词: stapling 第三人称单数: staples');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('panic', '[\'pænɪk]', 'n.惊慌；恐慌 v.使…惊慌；感到恐慌 adj.恐慌的；惊慌的', '1. There was a panic when the building caught fire. 大楼起火时, 人们一片惊慌。 2. Rumours of an imminent earthquake startled a panic. 谣传即将发生地震引起了一阵恐慌。 3. The thunder panicked the horse. 雷声使马受惊了。 4. The idea might panic the investors. 这个想法可能会使投资者惶恐不安。 5. The financial crisis caused panic selling of securities. 金融危机引发了恐慌之下的债权抛售。', '形容词: panicky 过去式: panicked 过去分词: panicked 现在分词: panicking 第三人称单数: panics');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consult', '[kən\'sʌlt]', 'v.查阅；请教；商讨；就诊', '1. I will have to consult the plane time table first. 我得先查阅飞机时刻表。 2. He paused to consult his notes, and then proceeded with his questions. 他停下来看了看笔记，然后继续提问。 3. If you wish good advice, consult an old man. 若要主意好，老人须请教。 4. I need to consult with my colleagues on the proposals. 我需要和我的同事商讨这些建议。', '名词: consulter 过去式: consulted 过去分词: consulted 现在分词: consulting 第三人称单数: consults');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meditative', '[\'medɪteɪtɪv]', 'adj.沉思的；冥想的；善於思考的', '1. She found him in a meditative mood. 她见他正在沉思。 2. She stood looking at him with meditative eyes. 她站着用沉思的目光打量他。 3. He is a meditative story-teller or romancer. 他是个善于深入思考的故事家。', '副词: meditatively 名词: meditativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('singe', '[sɪndʒ]', 'v.(轻微)烧焦；烫焦；损伤 n.烧焦', '1. The rug singed because it was too near the fire. 地毯太靠近壁炉已烤焦了。 2. The iron\'s too hot, you\'ll singe the dress. 熨斗太热了，你会把衣服烫焦的。 3. The last time we agree to help that company out of its difficulty, we singe our wing quite badly. 上次我们答应帮助那家公司摆脱困境时我们自己遭受了很大的损失。', '过去式: singed 过去分词: singed 现在分词: singeing 第三人称单数: singes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fervent', '[\'fɜːrvənt]', 'adj.热情的；强烈的；炎热的；热心的', '1. She had a fervent farewell speech. 她发表了热情的告别演说。 2. His mother kissed him a long, fervent kiss. 母亲给了他一个长时间的、热烈的吻。 3. She has a fervent desire to win. 她有著强烈的获胜欲望。 4. The lawyer made a fervent plea for clemency. 律师强烈要求从宽处理。', '副词: fervently 名词: ferventness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deny', '[dɪ\'naɪ]', 'vt.否认；拒绝承认；拒绝给予；自制', '1. He is not trustworthy, but at the same time, we cannot deny that he is clever. 他不可信赖,然而我们不能否认他很聪明。 2. He denied that it was his fault. 他拒不承认这是他的过错。 3. I was denied the chance of going to university. 我得不到上大学的机会。 4. We should try to deny ourselves from indulging in computer games. 我们应该尽力克制自己,不使自己沉溺于电脑游戏。', '过去式: denied 过去分词: denied 现在分词: denying 第三人称单数: denies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diverge', '[daɪ\'vɜːrdʒ]', 'v.分歧；分叉；[数]发散', '1. Our views diverged so greatly that it was impossible to agree. 我们的观点存在着严重的分歧，绝无调和余地。 2. These figures and the last ones diverge greatly. 这些数字与上次的数字有很大差异。 3. The stream diverges here. 小溪在这儿分岔。 4. Unfortunately, the iteration is easy to diverge and difficult to control. 计算时若初始形状与找形形状差异较大，则会使迭代计算发散。', '过去式: diverged 过去分词: diverged 现在分词: diverging 第三人称单数: diverges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relentless', '[rɪ\'lentləs]', 'adj.冷酷无情的；不间断的', '1. He was relentless in demanding repayment of the debt. 他冷酷无情地要求偿还那笔债。 2. However, in Antarctica, the elements are relentless. 然而，在南极洲，自然环境是冷酷无情的。 3. I\'m relentless in the pursuit of my goals. 我持续不断地追求我的目标。 4. The traffic noise is relentless. 车辆的噪音一刻也不停止。', '副词: relentlessly 名词: relentlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('encounter', '[ɪn\'kaʊntər]', 'n.意外的相见；邂逅；遭遇 v.遭遇；遇到；偶然碰到', '1. If both participate, it may be an actual encounter of bodiless consciousness. 如果是双向的，这会是一个真实的与灵魂的相见。 2. A fortunate encounter brought us together. 一次幸运的邂逅使我们相识。 3. It was a bloody encounter between the two armies. 这是那两军之间的一次激烈的遭遇战。 4. Don\'t be afraid to encounter risks. 不要害怕遭遇危险。', '过去式: encountered 过去分词: encountered 现在分词: encountering 第三人称单数: encounters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('particular', '[pər\'tɪkjələr]', 'adj.特定的；专指的；特殊的；特别的；挑剔的 n.详情；细节', '1. They depend on a particular historical situation. 它们取决于特定的历史境况。 2. I have nothing particular to do this evening. 今晚我没有什么特殊的事要做。 3. Clouds must be given a particular attention. 必须对云给予特别的注意。 4. She\'s very particular about what she wears. 她对衣著很讲究。 5. The account is correct in every particular. 所述的每一细节都正确无误。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('verse', '[vɜːrs]', 'n.诗；韵文；诗节 vi.作诗 vt.诗化；在诗中表现；对 ... 精通', '1. There are four verses in each poem. 每首诗有四个诗节。 2. She wrote most of her poetry in blank verse. 她所写的诗大部分都是无韵诗。 3. Most of the scenes are written in verse, but some are in prose. 这场戏大部分内容是用韵文写成的,但也有一些是散文形式的 4. There are four verses in each poem. 每首诗有四个诗节。 5. It was in blank verse that she sang. 她以无韵诗体作诗。', '过去式: versed 过去分词: versed 现在分词: versing 第三人称单数: verses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insulin', '[\'ɪnsəlɪn]', 'n.胰岛素', '1. They were all dependent on supplemental insulin. 他们都依赖于外源胰岛素。 2. The pancreas began churning out insulin. 胰腺开始产生胰岛素。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conspiracy', '[kən\'spɪrəsɪ]', 'n.阴谋；共谋', '1. He is a party to the conspiracy. 他参与了那次阴谋。 2. He revealed their conspiracy to overthrow the government. 他泄露了他们推翻政府的阴谋。 3. It has recently come to light that a second official was implicated in the conspiracy. 最近有消息披露：又有一名高级官员与这个阴谋有牵连。 4. She was convicted on an indictment for conspiracy. 她被控以共谋罪，罪名成立。', '名词复数: conspiracies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grasshopper', '[\'ɡræshɑːpər]', 'n.蚱蜢；蝗虫；轻型飞机；蚱蜢鸡尾酒', '1. The spider trapped a grasshopper in its web. 那蜘蛛在它的网上捕捉到了一只蚂蚱。 2. The mantis and grasshopper are small animals in the field. 螳螂和蚱蜢是田地里的小动物。 3. The grasshopper was cold and hungry. 蝗虫又冷又饿。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vulgar', '[\'vʌlɡər]', 'adj.通俗的；粗俗的；乡土的 n.平民，百姓', '1. Life is a vulgar flare amid the cool radiance. 生命只是惨淡的星光里的平凡的一闪. 2. The vice premier led a vulgar life in his hometown after he resigned. 那位副总理辞职后在故乡过着平民生活。 3. Her taste in clothing is rather vulgar. 她穿着相当俗气。 4. Putting food into one\'s mouth with a knife is considered vulgar in England. 在英国，用刀把食物送进嘴里被认为是粗鲁的行为。', '副词: vulgarly 名词: vulgarness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rumor', '[\'ruːmə]', 'n.谣言；传闻 vt.谣传 =<英>rumour', '1. I\'m rather bored by the rumor. 这谣传我真听厌烦了。 2. Despite persistent denials, the rumor continued to spread. 尽管一再否认，谣言还是不胫而走。 3. A rumor went forth that the price of eggs would be raised soon. 谣传近期鸡蛋要涨价。 4. The rumor was without foundation. 那条谣言毫无根据。 5. He is rumored to have escaped to Dublin. 据说他已逃往都柏林。', '过去式: rumored 过去分词: rumored 现在分词: rumoring 第三人称单数: rumors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nourish', '[\'nɜːrɪʃ]', 'v.滋养；给营养；培育；怀有', '1. They needed good food to nourish their bodies. 他们需要好食品滋养身体。 2. Milk is all we need to nourish a small baby. 我们供给婴儿营养只需喂奶就够了。 3. Most plants are nourished by water drawn up through their roots. 多数植物是靠着根吸收水分来维持生命的。 4. The school\'s goal is to nourish young musical talent. 这个学校的目标是培育年轻的音乐人才。', '名词: nourisher 过去式: nourished 过去分词: nourished 现在分词: nourishing 第三人称单数: nourishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rodeo', '[\'roʊdioʊ]', 'n.马术竞技表演会；将牛、马驱集在一起', '1. Riding bulls is always an exciting event at a rodeo. 骑公牛总是放牧人竞技会上激动人心的表演。 2. Bull riding and a wild horse race are big draws at the Big Rodeo. 驯牛和野马赛跑都是牛仔表演大会上的重头戏。 3. When you go to the Rodeo you get a real taste of life in the Midwest. 如果您有机会参加竞技会，您就可以体验到真正的中西部生活。 4. The 40-year-old rodeo cowboy decided to hang up his spurs and retire. 这名年届不惑的牛仔决定高挂马刺靴，过退休生活。', '名词复数: rodeos');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('audition', '[ɔː\'dɪʃn]', 'n.听；听力；试听；试镜 v.试音；试听；试镜', '1. Tone adjustment can meet different audtion environment. 音质调节功能能满足各种听音环境。 2. How does the hospital check audition commonly? 医院检查听力一般怎么检查的？ 3. They made an audition of the new recordings. 他们对新录制的材料进行了试听。 4. What do I need to prepare for my audition? 我需要为试镜准备什么? 5. Which part are you auditioning for? 你扮什么角色试音?', '过去式: auditioned 过去分词: auditioned 现在分词: auditioning 第三人称单数: auditions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('risk', '[rɪsk]', 'n.危险；风险；投资报酬的风险 vt.冒 ... 的危险；承受...的风险', '1. He saved my life at the risk of his own. 他冒着自己的生命危险救了我的命。 2. Investors in Central Asia have to face political risk. 在中亚,投资者还得面临政治风险。 3. Loans to farmers are now considered to be a bad risk. 贷款给农民现在被认为要承受糟糕的投资报酬风险。 4. If you don\'t warm up before taking exercise, you risk injuring yourself. 假如运动前不做准备活动,你就有受伤的危险。', '名词: risker 过去式: risked 过去分词: risked 现在分词: risking 第三人称单数: risks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('parasitic', '[ˌpærə\'sɪtɪk]', 'adj.寄生的；由寄生虫引起的；靠他人为生的 =parasitical.', '1. The mistletoe plant is a parasite on trees. 槲寄生是寄生在树上的植物。 2. The sporogonium is parasitic on the gametophyte generation. 孢子体是寄生在配子体上的。 3. More than two hundred million people suffer from this parasitic worm disease. 两亿多人口遭受着这种寄生蠕虫引起的疾病。 4. Parasitic and nonparasitic cysts rarely occur in the spleen. 寄生虫性和非寄生虫性囊肿在脾脏很少发生。', '副词: parasitically 异体字: parasitical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('critic', '[\'krɪtɪk]', 'n.评论家；批评家', '1. She is a very discerning art critic. 她是位眼光敏锐的艺术评论家。 2. He has a reputation for being a forthright critic. 他是以直率著称的评论家。 3. Have you read the article written by that famous critic? 你读过那个著名的批评家写的这篇文章吗？ 4. A critic is a man whose watch is five minutes ahead of other people\'s watch. 批评家，是一个他的表要比别人的表快上五分钟的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('psychology', '[saɪ\'kɑːlədʒi]', 'n.心理；心理学', '1. I can\'t understand that man\'s psychology. 我无法理解那个人的心理。 2. She had no personal life and no private psychology. 她没有个人的生活和隐秘的心理活动。 3. Many people failed in the psychology test. 很多人在心理测试环节被淘汰。 4. This is fluky psychology, also be pure belong to accidental. 这是侥幸心理，亦是纯属偶然。', '名词复数: psychologies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('president', '[\'prezɪdənt]', 'n.(国家)总统；(公司)总裁；校长；总经理；社长', '1. The president gave the Prince and his attendants a farewell banquet. 总统为王子和他的随员举行了告别宴会。 2. She was exalted to the position of president. 她被提升为校长。 3. The president has just come to see me. 校长刚才来看我来了。 4. When the president of the company retired, the vice-president was elevated to his position. 该公司的总经理退休时,副总经理被提升为总经理。', '名词: presidentship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('anomalous', '[ə\'nɑːmələs]', 'adj.反常的；不规则的', '1. The phenomenon is called anomalous propagation. 这种现象被称为异常传播。 2. He is in an anomalous position as the only part-time worker in the firm. 他与众不同，是公司里唯一的兼职人员。 3. The mechanism of this anomalous vascular response is unknown. 此种不规则的血管反应的机制尚不清楚。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('muddle', '[\'mʌdl]', 'n.混乱；糊涂 vt.使混乱；使糊涂；弄糟 vi.胡乱应付；混乱', '1. There was a muddle over our hotel accommodation. 我们旅馆的食宿安排十分混乱。 2. Your room\'s in a real muddle. 你的房间真是乱七八糟。 3. The old lady gets in(to) a muddle trying to work the video. 那老太太想开录像机，但是越搞越糊涂。 4. The cleaner had muddled my papers, and I couldn\'t find the one I wanted. 清洁工把我的文件弄乱了，我找不到我要的那份了。 5. We muddle along from day to day. 我们一天天地混日子。', '名词: muddler 过去式: muddled 过去分词: muddled 现在分词: muddling 第三人称单数: muddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mine', '[maɪn]', 'pron.我的 n.矿；地雷；矿藏 v.采矿；用地雷炸', '1. He is a distant cousin of mine. 他是我的一位远房表亲。 2. The mine was closed owing to exhaustion. 这个煤矿因矿源枯竭而被关闭。 3. The ship\'s bow was blown off by a mine. 船头给一枚水雷炸掉了。 4. A good encyclopaedia is a mine of information. 一部好的百科全书是一座知识宝库。 5. Peopel still mine for coal in this area. 人们还在这个地区开采煤矿。', '过去式: mined 过去分词: mined 现在分词: mining 第三人称单数: mines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('baggage', '[\'bæɡɪdʒ]', 'n.行李', '1. Let me put your baggage in the trunk. 我来把你的行李放在汽车后部的行李箱内。 2. Our baggage has cleared customs. 我们的行李已通过海关检查。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cramped', '[kræmpt]', 'adj.狭窄的；束缚的；难认的', '1. Our accommodation is rather cramped. 我们住的地方很挤。 2. The house was terribly small and cramped, but the agent described it as a bijou residence. 房子十分狭小拥挤，但经纪人却把它说成是小巧别致的住宅。 3. I feel cramped by the limitations of my job. 我觉得受工作束缚,没有什么奔头儿。 4. And it was no longer the same cramped, awkward handwriting as before 他的笔迹，也不像先前那样扭曲拙笨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emaciate', '[ɪ\'meɪʃɪˌeɪt]', 'v.(使)消瘦；(使)憔悴', '1. To cause to become lean,usually by starvation; emaciate. 使消瘦通常通过饥饿使变瘦；使消瘦 2. To cause to become lean, usually by starvation; emaciate. 使消瘦通常通过饥饿使变瘦；使消瘦 3. To cause to become lean, usually by starvation;emaciate. 使消瘦通常通过饥饿使变瘦； 4. emaciate bodies 使身体瘦弱', '名词: emaciation 过去式: emaciated 过去分词: emaciated 现在分词: emaciating 第三人称单数: emaciates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bulk', '[bʌlk]', 'n.体积；容积；大块；大部分；大批 adj.散装的；大量的 vt.使膨胀；使成堆 vi.膨胀；显得重要', '1. It\'s not their weight that makes these sacks hard to carry, it\'s their bulk. 这些袋子难以搬运,倒不是因为重而是体积太大。 2. He heaved his huge bulk out of the chair. 他挺起巨大的身躯，从椅子上站了起来。 3. The bulk of the work has already been done. 大部分工作已经完成。 4. The great bulk of necessary work can never be anything but painful. 大量必须做的工作真令人痛苦。 5. We can manage some bulk carrier within two week. 我们可在两周内安排一些散装船去。 6. A dozen petticoats bulked out her figure. 十几条衬裙把她的身体撑得圆鼓鼓的。 7. The cake bulked up. 蛋糕发起来了。', '过去式: bulked 过去分词: bulked 现在分词: bulking 第三人称单数: bulks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ridge', '[rɪdʒ]', 'n.脊；山脊；山脉；隆起部 v.（使）成山脊', '1. Recurvature follows after it traverses the ridge axis. 预料尼伯特将于横过副高脊线后开始转向。 2. Riding on the ridge of the bridge, the proud bride shouts loudly to the cloud. 骄傲的新娘骑在桥脊上对着云大声喊。 3. He walked along the mountain ridge. 他顺着山脊走。 4. The evening before the battle, Wellington took up a defensive position along, and to the rear of, a long ridge. 那场战斗的前夜，威灵顿沿一条长长的山脊背后占据了一个防守阵地。 5. The floor of the Atlantic ridges in the middle from north to south. 大西洋洋底在中部形成由北向南的海脊。', '过去式: ridged 过去分词: ridged 现在分词: ridging 第三人称单数: ridges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rend', '[rend]', 'v.撕破；分裂；劈开；强夺', '1. Wolves will rend a lamb to pieces . 狼群会把一只羔羊撕成碎片。 2. The stillness was rent by thunderous applause. 雷鸣般的掌声打破了寂静。 3. The party was rent in two. 这个政党分裂成两派。 4. The integrated country will rend into several independent regions sooner or later. 那个完整的国家早晚会分裂成几个独立的地区。', '过去式: rent/rended 过去分词: rent/rended 现在分词: rending 第三人称单数: rends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('terminate', '[\'tɜːmɪneɪt]', 'v.结束；终止；满期；达到终点', '1. Communist Party of China terminated the rule of feudal landlord class. 中国共产党结束了封建地主阶级的统治。 2. Your contract has been terminated. 你的合同已经被终止。 3. We have to terminate this contract. 我们不得不终止这个合同。 4. The contract will terminate soon. 契约快要期满了。', '过去式: terminated 过去分词: terminated 现在分词: terminating 第三人称单数: terminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cavity', '[\'kævəti]', 'n.洞；空穴；腔；蛀洞', '1. I have a toothache because there is a cavity in one of my teeth. 我牙疼，因为我的一颗牙齿上有个洞。 2. He jammed the material in until the cavity was full. 他用力把材料塞进去，直到空穴完全填满。 3. The peritoneal cavity is a closed sac. 腹膜腔是一个封闭的囊腔。 4. The tumor growing in the enteric cavity blocked excretion of food. 肿瘤在肠腔里生长阻碍了食物排泄。', '名词复数: cavities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('condone', '[kən\'doʊn]', 'vt.宽恕', '1. People cannot condone the use of fierce violence. 人们不能宽恕使用凶残的暴力。 2. No faith or culture should condone the outrages against them. 任何信仰或文化都不能宽恕对妇幼施加的暴行。', '名词: condoner 过去式: condoned 过去分词: condoned 现在分词: condoning 第三人称单数: condones');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pictorial', '[pɪk\'tɔːriəl]', 'adj.绘画的；用图片的 n.画报', '1. We have quite a variety of pictorial story books. 我们有许多连环画图书。 2. They have insist on a full pictorial coverage of the event. 他们坚持要用图片来报导这些事件。 3. The pretty girl on the cover of the pictorial is just a sales gimmick. 画报的封面上印上美女不过是吸引顾客的一种生意眼。 4. If that is not a pictorial, then it is a magazine. 那不是画报就是杂志。', '副词: pictorially 名词: pictoriality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scare', '[sker]', 'v.受惊吓；恐吓；吓走 n.惊吓；惊恐', '1. You scare them to death with your mouth. 你一开口就能把人吓死。 2. We\'ll scare her out of telling the police. 我们要把她吓得不敢报警。 3. His threats scared them out of carrying out the plan. 他的威胁迫使他们不敢实行该计划。 4. The dog scared the thief away. 狗把小偷吓走了。 5. You did give me a scare. 你真吓了我一跳。', '名词: scarer 过去式: scared 过去分词: scared 现在分词: scaring 第三人称单数: scares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unravel', '[ʌn\'rævl]', 'v.解开；阐明；解释；破坏(计划、安排等)', '1. My knitting has unravelled. 我编织的东西散开了。 2. The baby unraveled its mother\'s knitting. 那婴儿将母亲的编织物拆散了。 3. One wrong move and the reef could unravel in a day. 一个措施不对，这块珊瑚礁就可能在一天之内分崩离析。 4. There is still a good deal to unravel. 还有不少问题要澄清。', '过去式: unraveled/unravelled 过去分词: unraveled/unravelled 现在分词: unraveling/unravelling 第三人称单数: unravels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flourish', '[\'flɜːrɪʃ]', 'v.茂盛；繁荣；挥舞；活跃 n.挥舞；花样；炫耀；华丽词藻', '1. There were two or three palm trees flourishing in the promenade garden. 街心花园里有两三棵枝繁叶茂的棕榈树。 2. Plants will not flourish without water. 没有水植物就不会长得茂盛。 3. These plants flourish in a damp climate. 这些植物在潮湿的气候下长势茂盛。 4. Our business seemed to flourish. 我们在生意看上去很兴隆。 5. She rode by with a flourish of her whip. 她骑马挥鞭而过。', '名词: flourisher 过去式: flourished 过去分词: flourished 现在分词: flourishing 第三人称单数: flourishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aviator', '[\'eɪvieɪtər]', 'n.飞行员', '1. He is a daring aviator. 他是一个勇敢的飞行家。 2. The aviator warped a wing tip to regain balance . 飞行员使一机翼的端部翘起，以恢复平衡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('debut', '[deɪ\'bjuː]', 'n.首次露面；初次登场 v.初次登场；首次推出', '1. His debut marks him out for future success. 他的首次亮相预示了将来的成功。 2. He will make his debut for the first team this week. 本周他将在第一支出场的队伍中首次亮相。 3. She made a successful debut. 她初次登台获得成功。 4. The young actress made her debut in the new comedy. 这位年轻的女演员在新上演的喜剧里首次登台演出。 5. A new product will debut next week. 一种新产品将在下周面世。', '过去式: debuted 过去分词: debuted 现在分词: debuting 第三人称单数: debuts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clutter', '[\'klʌtər]', 'vt.弄乱；混乱 n.杂乱', '1. Don\'t clutter up my desk. I\'ve just tidied it. 不要在我的书桌上乱放东西,我刚收拾好。 2. Her belongings clutter up my bedroom. 她的东西乱七八糟堆满在我卧室里。 3. Don\'t clutter the page with too many diagrams. 别用太多的图表来堆砌版面。 4. His room is in a clutter so I have to tidy it up. 他的房间乱七八糟的，我不得不整理一下。', '过去式: cluttered 过去分词: cluttered 现在分词: cluttering 第三人称单数: clutters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('camouflage', '[\'kæməflɑːʒ]', 'n.伪装；掩饰；迷彩服 v.伪装；欺瞒', '1. They used branches of trees as camouflage. 他们用树枝做伪装。 2. The animal\'s markings provide effective camouflage. 这种动物身上的斑纹是很有效的伪装。 3. Interestingly, Jaguar has attempted to disguise the prototype as a BMW, even adopting the same psychedelic camouflage material as its German rival. 有趣的是，捷豹一直试图掩饰的原型作为一个宝马，即使采用同样的迷幻伪装材料作为其德国竞争对手。 4. Some of them even wore them with their camouflage combat smocks. 有些人还穿着迷彩服佩带勋章。 5. They used branches of trees as camouflage. 他们用树枝做伪装。', '名词: camouflager 过去式: camouflaged 过去分词: camouflaged 现在分词: camouflaging 第三人称单数: camouflages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hurricane', '[\'hɜːrəkən]', 'n.飓风；暴风', '1. The hurricane destroyed the whole village. 飓风把整个村子都毁掉了。 2. The hurricane screamed outside. 外面飓风呼啸著。 3. The hurricane has a speed of 73 miles per hour. 飓风每小时73英里。 4. The radio alerted the citizens to prepare for the hurricane. 电台警告市民们作好预防暴风准备。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('initiate', '[ɪ\'nɪʃieɪt]', 'vt.开始；创始；启蒙；介绍加入 n.创始人 adj.新加入的；启蒙的', '1. This term we will initiate a new teaching plan. 这学期我们将开始实行一个新的教学计划。 2. The company initiated a management training program for small businesses. 该公司发起了针对小企业的管理培训方案。 3. I shall initiate you into our business methods. 我将把我们的营业方法介绍给你。 4. My father wanted to initiate me into fishing. 我爸爸想教我钓鱼。', '名词: initiator 过去式: initiated 过去分词: initiated 现在分词: initiating 第三人称单数: initiates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stationary', '[\'steɪʃəneri]', 'adj.静止的，不动的；稳定的 n.驻军', '1. He crashed into a stationary bus. 他撞了一辆停着不动的公共汽车。 2. A stationary object is easy to be aimed at. 一个静止不动的物体是容易瞄准的。 3. An astronaut will attempt to leave the stationary spaceship and then return to it. 一名宇航员试着离开静止不动的宇宙飞船，然后再返回。', '名词: stationariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enunciate', '[ɪ\'nʌnsieɪt]', 'v.清晰地发音；(清楚地)表达；阐述，宣布', '1. She enunciated each word slowly for her students. 她把每个字都给学生慢慢念清楚。 2. That actor enunciates very well. 那演员发音很清晰。 3. He is always willing to enunciate his opinions on the subject of politics. 他总是愿意对政治问题发表意见。', '形容词: enunciable 副词: enunciatively 名词: enunciation 过去式: enunciated 过去分词: enunciated 现在分词: enunciating 第三人称单数: enunciates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('Latin', '[\'lætn]', 'n.拉丁语；拉丁人 adj.拉丁语的；拉丁人的；拉丁语系国家的', '1. Many languages have Latin as their base. 许多语言都以拉丁语为基础。 2. I can\'t get this Latin grammar into my head. 我理解不了这条拉丁语语法规则。 3. The reign of the Latin mind was now drawing to an end. 拉丁人思想的统治现在即将结束。 4. Very few students learn Latin now. 现在学拉丁语的学生少得很。', '动词: latinize 副词: latine');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clean', '[kliːn]', 'adj.干净的；纯洁的；完全的；空白的；正当的；精准的 adv.完全地 n.清洁 v.打扫；清扫；擦，刷', '1. You must keep your clothes clean. 你必须保持衣着整洁。 2. I\'ll let you use my bike on condition that you keep it clean. 如果你能保持车子干净,我就让你用我的自行车。 3. Mickey is a clean mouse right from the beginning. 米老鼠从一开始就是一只纯洁的老鼠。 4. President Bush writes a personal letter to Kim, in essence entreating him to come clean on his nuclear program so we can proceed to full normalization. 布什总统给金正日写了一封私人信件，主要是要求他澄清核项目，这样我们可以和他们继续推进完全的正常化关系。 5. I clean forgot about it. 我完全忘记了这件事。 6. The housewife always keeps the sink clean. 主妇总是保持水槽的清洁。 7. Please clean the window as I can hardly see out. 请把窗子弄干净，我几乎看不到外面。', '形容词: cleanable 比较级: cleaner 最高级: cleanest 名词: cleanness 过去式: cleaned 过去分词: cleaned 现在分词: cleaning 第三人称单数: cleans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subtle', '[\'sʌtl]', 'adj.微妙的；敏锐的；不明显的；精细的；狡猾的', '1. There were subtle hints in his letter. 他的信中有些微妙的暗示。 2. What meaning will my subtle signal make? 我的微妙信号表达了什么意思? 3. She has a very subtle mind. 她有个很敏锐的头脑。 4. Satire is a high and subtle art. 讽刺是一门崇高而又含蓄的艺术。', '副词: subtly 比较级: subtler 最高级: subtlest 名词: subtleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('content', '[\'kɑːntent]', 'n. 内容； 目录； 含量 adj. 满足的； 满意的 vt. 使 ... 满足； 使 ... 安心', '1. Teaching content should be concise. 教学内容要少而精。 2. The book is rich in content and succinct in style. 这本书内容丰富，文字简练。 3. Define content sections of status reports. 定义状态报告的目录部分。 4. Using file shares that provide only a hierarchical directory structure as a means of organizing content. 将只提供一个层次目录结构的文件共享作为内容组织方式使用。 5. We\'re also in the content business. 我们是也在满足的生意方面。 6. Disport oneself to one\'s heart\'s content. 玩个痛快什么也不会使他满足。', '过去式: contented 过去分词: contented 现在分词: contenting 第三人称单数: contents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subordinate', '[sə\'bɔːrdɪnət]', 'adj.下级的；次要的 n.属下；附属物 vt.使服从；把 ... 放在次要', '1. He is a subordinate officer. 他是位下级军官。 2. She works in the subordinate hospital of our universtiy. 她在我们学校的附属医院工作。 3. All the other issues are subordinate to this one. 所有问题都要以这个问题为主。 4. He was always friendly to his subordinates. 他对下级一向和蔼可亲。 5. He subordinated his wishes to the general good of the group. 他使自己的愿望服从于集体的利益。', '形容词: subordinative 副词: subordinately 名词: subordinateness 过去式: subordinated 过去分词: subordinated 现在分词: subordinating 第三人称单数: subordinates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delineate', '[dɪ\'lɪnieɪt]', 'vt.描绘；叙述；画出', '1. Control uses steps to delineate different sections of user data input. 控件使用多个步骤来描绘用户数据输入的不同部分。 2. You can use semicolons to delineate multiple filter patterns within a filter option. 您可以使用分号来描绘一个筛选选项中的多个筛选模式。', '形容词: delineative 名词: delineation 过去式: delineated 过去分词: delineated 现在分词: delineating 第三人称单数: delineates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('null', '[nʌl]', 'adj.无效的；无价值的；无效力的 n.零；空 vt.使无效', '1. Their actions rendered the contract null and void. 他们的行为使合同无效。 2. The marriage was declared null and void. 婚姻已宣告无效了。 3. The path must end with a null character. 该路经必须以零结尾。 4. Vomit in null gravity wouldn\'t be fun. 如果在零重力下呕吐了可不是件好笑的事。', '过去式: nulled 过去分词: nulled 现在分词: nulling 第三人称单数: nulls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exaggerate', '[ɪɡ\'zædʒəreɪt]', 'vt.夸张；夸大；对...言过其实 vi.夸张；夸大其词', '1. Don\'t exaggerate the parallelism between the two cases. 不要夸大那两件事的相似性。 2. The seriousness of the situation has been much exaggerated by the press. 形势的严重性被报纸夸大了。 3. He tends to exaggerate the difficulties. 他往往夸大困难。 4. We should neither exaggerate nor ignore the differences. 虽然我们不能夸大这些不同，但是我们也不能忽视它们的存在。 5. If you exaggerate, you will sound fantastically American. 如果你发音夸张听起来会特别有美国味。', '形容词: exaggerative 副词: exaggeratedly 名词: exaggeration 过去式: exaggerated 过去分词: exaggerated 现在分词: exaggerating 第三人称单数: exaggerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('subtract', '[səb\'trækt]', 'vt.减去 vi.减少', '1. If you subtract 2 from 8, you get 6. 8减去2是6。 2. Please subtract a quarter of the money for your own use. 请扣除四分之一的钱由你自己支配使用。 3. The little girl has begin to learn to add and subtract. 这小女孩已在学做加减法了。', '名词: subtracter 过去式: subtracted 过去分词: subtracted 现在分词: subtracting 第三人称单数: subtracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('utter', '[\'ʌtər]', 'adj.完全的；全然的；绝对的 v.说；发出；表达', '1. It\'s an utter mystery. 这完全是个谜。 2. What utter rubbish he talks! 他完全是胡说！ 3. A feeling of utter helplessness washed over him. 一种全然无助的感觉涌上他的心头。 4. He wanted to impress this man with his utter willingness to comply and obey. 他要这个人觉得他的绝对屈服与服从。 5. How can you utter such falsehoods? 你怎么能说出这种谎言？', '形容词: utterable 名词: utterer 过去式: uttered 过去分词: uttered 现在分词: uttering 第三人称单数: utters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('curious', '[\'kjʊriəs]', 'adj.好奇的；奇特的', '1. I am curious how she will receive the news. 我很想知道她如何接受那消息。 2. The boy was curious about everything he saw. 那男孩对所见的一切都感到好奇。 3. I caught a curious sound in the neighboring room. 我听到隔壁房间里有奇怪的响声。 4. It\'s curious that he didn\'t tell you. 他没有告诉你，实在反常。', '副词: curiously 名词: curiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allude', '[ə\'luːd]', 'v.暗示；暗指', '1. I didn\'t allude to anything or anybody. 我并未影射任何人或任何事。 2. He did not even allude to his brother\'s engagement to Mary. 他兄弟与玛丽订婚的事他只字未提。 3. What were you alluding to just now? 你刚才指的是什么？', '过去式: alluded 过去分词: alluded 现在分词: alluding 第三人称单数: alludes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decry', '[dɪ\'kraɪ]', 'v.责难；诽谤', '1. Many people decry flogging. 许多人反对鞭打。 2. All the mayors decry gambling in all its forms. 所有市长都谴责各式各样的赌博。 3. Environmental activists decry destruction in Amazon. 环保人士谴责破坏亚马逊热带雨林的活动。', '名词: decrier 过去式: decried 过去分词: decried 现在分词: decrying 第三人称单数: decries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proportion', '[prə\'pɔːrʃn]', 'n.部分；比例；均衡；（复）规模 vt.使成比例；使均衡；分摊', '1. A large proportion of my time is spent in studying. 我的大部分时间花在学习上。 2. This door is narrow in proportion to its height. 这扇门就其高度的比例而言窄了些。 3. The two windows are in admirable proportion. 这两扇窗户十分相称. 4. The tree can grow to massive proportions. 这课树可以长到很大。 5. We must proportion the punishment to the crime . 我们必须使刑罚与罪行相当。', '形容词: proportionable 副词: proportionably 名词: proportioner 过去式: proportioned 过去分词: proportioned 现在分词: proportioning 第三人称单数: proportions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lease', '[liːs]', 'n.租约；租契；租期 vt.出租；租得', '1. Our present lease on the flat expires next month. 我们这套公寓的租约下月到期。 2. An astute tenant always reads the small print in a lease. 精明的租户对租契上的每个细小之处都要讲究。 3. Does your current lease provide for showings prior to the tenant vacating the property? 您当前的租契是否规定了在房客搬出房间之前可以提前展售？ 4. The lease of my house has only a year to run . 我的房子的租约期限只有1年了。 5. This company leases out property. 这个公司出租房地产。', '形容词: leasable 名词: leaser 过去式: leased 过去分词: leased 现在分词: leasing 第三人称单数: leases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conductor', '[kən\'dʌktər]', 'n.售票员；导体；指挥', '1. The conductor punched his bus ticket. 售票员用剪票夹在他的汽车票上打孔。 2. She knows why the metal is the good conductor. 她知道金属为什么是好的导体。 3. Rubber is not a conductor, and neither is plastics. 橡胶不是导体，塑料也不是导体。 4. With his baton the conductor was beating time. 指挥用指挥棒打着拍节。', '形容词: conductorial 名词: conductorship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ceremonious', '[ˌserə\'moʊniəs]', 'adj.拘礼的；礼节性的；正式的', '1. Putting on a hat can be a ceremonious act, an elegant gesture in the ritual of dressing. 戴帽子被看作一种礼节性的举动，是着装仪式上一个优雅的举动。', '副词: ceremoniously 名词: ceremoniousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('finch', '[fɪntʃ]', 'n.雀类', '1. This behaviour is commonly observed among several species of finch. 这种行为常常可以在几种雀科鸣禽中看到。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interplay', '[\'ɪntərpleɪ]', 'n.相互影响', '1. The exhibits also show the interplay of the LAPD and Hollywood. 该展览也向我们展示了洛杉矶警署和好莱坞之间的关系。 2. The story of our lives is the interplay of the bucket and the dipper. 我们的生活里充满了桶和舀水杯的交织。 3. The interplay between these elements is intriguing, and draws us in. 这些要素的交互作用十分引人入胜,也深深吸引着我们。 4. She examines the interplay between changing gender divisions and urban change. 她研究性别差异的变化和城市变化之间的相互影响。', '过去式: interplayed 过去分词: interplayed 现在分词: interplaying 第三人称单数: interplays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devastate', '[\'devəsteɪt]', 'vt.毁坏；使荒芜；使震惊', '1. They intended to devastate the town at one stroke. 他们企图一举摧毁全城。 2. Our Embassy was devastated by three bombs of NATO. 我们的使馆被北约的三枚炸弹炸毁了。 3. The country was devastated by a long war. 该国因遭到长期战争的破坏而荒废。 4. I was devastated by the news of the wreck. 我获悉失事的消息感到十分震惊。', '副词: devastatingly 名词: devastation 过去式: devastated 过去分词: devastated 现在分词: devastating 第三人称单数: devastates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('steadfast', '[\'stedfæst]', 'adj.坚定的；毫不动摇的', '1. Our nation is patient and steadfast. 我们的国家是有耐心的，立场是坚定的。 2. He adopted a steadfast attitude towards this issue. 他对这件事采取坚定的态度。 3. He is of a resolute and steadfast disposition. 他的性格非常刚毅。', '副词: steadfastly 名词: steadfastness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('female', '[\'fiːmeɪl]', 'adj.女性的；雌性的 n.女性；雌性动物；[植]雌株', '1. The male and female genders are equal. 男性和女性是平等的。 2. All the female workers in this factory got a present on March 8th. 这家工厂的所有女职工在三八节都得到了一份礼物。 3. The male sperm fertilizes the female egg. 雄性的精子使雌性的卵子受精。 4. The male is physically stronger than the female. 男性在身体上要比女性强壮。', '名词: femaleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('illegible', '[ɪ\'ledʒəbl]', 'adj.难辨认的；(字迹)模糊的', '1. The lettering on the gravestone was badly worn and almost illegible. 墓碑上的文字已严重磨损难以辨认。 2. Her signature was an illegible scrawl. 她的签字潦草难辩。 3. The writing is illegible; I cannot read what it says. 字迹不清楚，我看不清上面写的是什么。', '副词: illegibly 名词: illegibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stretch', '[stretʃ]', 'v.伸展；延伸；张开；夸大 n.伸展；张开；弹性；一段时间；<俚>刑期 adj.可伸缩的', '1. Vast meadows stretch to the east. 辽阔的草场向东伸展。 2. She stretched across the table for the butter. 她探身去取放在餐桌对面的黄油。 3. The landscape seemed to stretch into infinity. 风景似乎延伸到了无穷远处。 4. Feeling intense fellowship with all human beings, she wished to throw herself into their arms, thinking that they would stretch them out to receive her. 她对所有的人怀着亲如手足的感情，她希望投身于他们的怀抱，以为他们会张开双臂接纳她。 5. I got out of the bed and had a good stretch. 我起床后舒服地伸了个懒腰。', '形容词: stretchable 名词: stretchability 过去式: stretched 过去分词: stretched 现在分词: stretching 第三人称单数: stretches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conduct', '[kən\'dʌkt]', 'n.行为；举动；品行 v.引导；指挥；管理 vt.导电；传热', '1. Your conduct is not consistent with what you say. 你的言行不一致。 2. His behavior transgressed the unwritten rules of social conduct. 他的行为违反了不成文的社交规范。 3. His conduct roused the suspicion of the police. 他的举动引起了警察的怀疑。 4. He has good conduct. 他品行端正。 5. The guide conducted us around the ruins of the ancient city. 导游引导我们游览了古城废墟。 6. Most metals can conduct electricity. 大多数金属能导电。', '形容词: conductible 名词: conductibility 过去式: conducted 过去分词: conducted 现在分词: conducting 第三人称单数: conducts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stain', '[steɪn]', 'n.污点；瑕疵；着色剂；染料 v.弄脏；玷污；着色', '1. The stain on his shirt is difficult to clean off. 他衬衣上的污点很难去除掉。 2. It will remain an indelible stain on his memory. 这将成为他记忆中一个不可磨灭的污点。 3. Such a man is a stain to humanity. 这种人是人类的耻辱。 4. There isn\'t a stain on her reputation. 她的名誉没有半点瑕疵。 5. These carpets won\'t stain easily. 这些地毯不易弄脏。', '形容词: stainable 名词: stainer 过去式: stained 过去分词: stained 现在分词: staining 第三人称单数: stains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consistent', '[kən\'sɪstənt]', 'adj.始终如一的；持续的；一致的', '1. She is a consistent girl in her feeling. 在感情方面她是个始终如一的女孩。 2. Our aim is to ensure a consistent growth. 我们的目标是确保持续的增长。 3. Your conduct is not consistent with what you say. 你的言行不一致。', '副词: consistently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distant', '[\'dɪstənt]', 'adj.疏远的；遥远的；远房的；陌生的；远行的', '1. His stepson is still very distant towards him. 他的继子对他仍然很疏远。 2. Her manner was cold and distant. 她的态度冷漠而疏远。 3. It snows all the year round in that distant little village. 在那个遥远的小村落里整年下雪。 4. This palmer came from a very distant place. 这个朝圣者来自非常远的地方。', '副词: distantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ambitious', '[æm\'bɪʃəs]', 'adj.有雄心的；野心勃勃的；有抱负的', '1. Mr. Lin is an ambitious businessman. 林先生是个有雄心的生意人。 2. I ought to do something a bit more ambitious. 我应当做些更有雄心的事。 3. They ventured on an ambitious program of reform. 他们冒然采取一项野心勃勃的改革计划。 4. The ambitious boy learned very quickly. 那位有抱负的少年学得很快。', '副词: ambitiously 名词: ambitiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enrapture', '[ɪn\'ræptʃər]', 'vt.使狂喜；使出神', '1. We were enraptured by the view of the mountains. 我们看到山峦景色，心花怒放。', '名词: enrapturement 过去式: enraptured 过去分词: enraptured 现在分词: enrapturing 第三人称单数: enraptures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bald', '[bɔːld]', 'adj.秃头的；单调的；无装饰的 v.（使）变秃头', '1. He shaved his head bald. 他剃了个光头。 2. He has a shiny bald pate. 他是个亮光光的秃顶。 3. We planted some trees on the bald hill. 我们在一座秃山上种了些树。 4. He took off the hat and revealed his bald head. 他脱下帽子，露出秃头。 5. I am starting to bald noticeably. 我头顶明显地开始变秃了。', '副词: baldly 比较级: balder 最高级: baldest 名词: baldness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impending', '[ɪm\'pendɪŋ]', 'adj.即将发生的；迫在眉睫的 动词impend的现在分词.', '1. The dark clouds suggest an impending storm. 乌云表明暴风雨即将来临。 2. He was inadequately prepared for the impending examinations. 他对即将举行的考试准备不足。 3. She was keyed up over her impending operation. 她为了即将进行的手术而心中忐忑不安。 4. We are not in denial of impending, dreadful possibilities. 我们并不否认有随时发生可怕情况的可能性。 5. Hurricane is impending. 台风就要来了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('engross', '[ɪn\'ɡroʊs]', 'v.使全神贯注；独占；正式誊写；用大字体书写', '1. She was engrossed in painting. 她全神贯注于绘画。 2. Engrossed in his book he forgot the time. 他全神贯注地看书忘记了时间。 3. She used to tell me that she thought I ought to expect some gratification from him for my company, for indeed he did, as it were, engross me. 她常对我说应该从他那里得到一些好处，做为我陪伴他的报酬，因为他的确好象独占了我。 4. He can\'t engross all the money. 他独占所有的钱是不可能的。', '名词: engrosser 过去式: engrossed 过去分词: engrossed 现在分词: engrossing 第三人称单数: engrosses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fishy', '[\'fɪʃi]', 'adj.（味道或气味）象鱼的；可疑的', '1. Something fishy is going on here. 一些可疑的事正在这里发生。 2. The pretext was weak, even fishy. 借口是站不住脚的，甚至是可疑的。', '副词: fishily 比较级: fishier 最高级: fishiest 名词: fishiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hardheaded', '[\'hɑːd\'hedɪd]', 'adj.顽固的；现实的；冷静的；脚踏实地的', '1. Hardheaded solve a few problems. 脚踏实地解决一些问题。 2. If you weren\'t so hardheaded, maybe I could teach you something. 假如你不是那么顽固,也许我可以教你点儿什么。 3. Have you ever been described as stubborn or hardheaded? By whom? 你被人说过固执吗？是谁说的？ 4. A word that Wang Shutong likes most is: Dreamy Gao Yuan, hardheaded. 王树彤最喜欢的一句话是：梦想高远，脚踏实地。', '副词: hardheadedly 名词: hardheadedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('interpret', '[ɪn\'tɜːrprɪt]', 'v.口译；解释；翻译；诠释', '1. To interpret at the UN is a difficult task. 在联合国做口译是件难 度很大的差事. 2. We need somebody to interpret from Russian into English. 我们需要一个把俄语口译为英语的人。 3. She interpret his silence as arrogance. 她把他的沉默解释为傲慢。 4. The guide interpreted the woman\'s remarks for us. 向导把那个女人的话翻译给我们听。', '形容词: interpretable 名词: interpretability 过去式: interpreted 过去分词: interpreted 现在分词: interpreting 第三人称单数: interprets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('calamity', '[kə\'læməti]', 'n.灾难；不幸事件', '1. The recent flooding in the south was a calamity. 最近南方的洪水是一场灾难。 2. She is always on the alert for some new calamity. 她总是保持警觉以防某种新的灾难。', '名词复数: calamities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coarse', '[kɔːrs]', 'adj.粗糙的；粗俗的；非精制的', '1. The medicine powder is too coarse, keep grinding it. 药面太粗了，再磨细点。 2. His coarse manners shocked everyone. 他的粗鲁的举止使每个人震惊。', '副词: coarsely 比较级: coarser 最高级: coarsest 名词: coarseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seize', '[siːz]', 'v.抓住；夺取；利用；没收', '1. Seize the chance, otherwise you\'ll regret it. 抓住这个机会，否则你会后悔的。 2. Before he could run away, she seized him by the collar. 在他逃跑之前,她抓住了他的衣领。 3. In a climate of political unrest, a dictator can often seize power. 在动荡的政治气候下,独裁者常常能夺取政权。 4. He would seize upon any excuse to justify himself. 他会利用任何借口为自己辩解。', '形容词: seizable 名词: seizer 过去式: seized 过去分词: seized 现在分词: seizing 第三人称单数: seizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('syllable', '[\'sɪləbl]', 'n.音节 vt.分音节', '1. The accent falls on the third syllable. 重音落在第三个音节上。 2. You put too much emphasis on the last syllable. 你把最后一个音节读得太重。', '过去式: syllabled 过去分词: syllabled 现在分词: syllabling 第三人称单数: syllables');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('generation', '[ˌdʒenə\'reɪʃn]', 'n.代；（产品类型的）代；产生；繁殖', '1. There is a generation gap between my parents and I. 我父母和我之间有代沟。 2. One generation blows bubbles, and the next breaks them. 前一代人制造出来的空洞理论，下一代人把它们打破。 3. Their visionary ideas are often misunderstood by their own generation. 他们有远见的理想往往招致同时代人的误解。 4. Each generation has its own standards of judgement. 每一代都有它自己的判断标准。', '形容词: generational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flame', '[fleɪm]', 'n.火焰；热情；燃烧；情人 v.燃烧；爆发；面红', '1. The candle flame flickered and went out. 烛火摇曳着，随即熄灭了。 2. Billows of flame swept through the forest. 熊熊烈火席卷森林。 3. He and I were kindled by a great flame of patriotism. 我和他由于一股爱国主义的热情都激动起来了。 4. It\'s been dry for so long that the forest could burst into flame at any moment. 天气干燥了这么久，森林随时都会燃烧起来。 5. The evening sky flamed with red and orange. 傍晚天空的颜色是一片火红和橘黄相间。', '名词: flamer 过去式: flamed 过去分词: flamed 现在分词: flaming 第三人称单数: flames');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('offer', '[\'ɔːfər]', 'vt.提供；提出；（卖方）出价；贡献 vi.提议；出现；求婚 n.提议；出价', '1. We offer a free backup service to customers. 对顾客我们提供免费配套服务。 2. Can you offer any evidence in support of what you have said? 你能提出证据来印证你讲的话吗？ 3. We offered 100,000 for the warehouse, but another company outbid us. 我们出价1000,000英镑购买这个库房,但另一家公司出价高于我们。 4. China is a fascinating country. It has a lot to offer the world. 中国是个迷人的国家,她对世界的贡献是巨大的。 5. He offered to pay $1,000 for the second-hand car. 他提议付1,000美元买那辆二手车。 6. He will probably refuse the offer. 他很可能会拒绝这一提议。', '名词: offerer 过去式: offered 过去分词: offered 现在分词: offering 第三人称单数: offers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('secure', '[sə\'kjʊr]', 'adj.安全的；牢靠的；稳妥的 vt.使安全；获得；固定', '1. If you are not sure it is secure, do not debug it. 如果您不能确定它是安全的,请不要调试它。 2. His place in history is now secure. 他在历史上的地位现在已经稳固了。 3. A climber needs secure footholds. 攀登的人脚踩的地方要很牢固。 4. We must create a secure and reliable international environment of lasting peace and stability. 我们要创造安全可靠、长期稳定的国际和平环境。 5. Some measures are needed to secure the farmland against shift sand. 需要采取措施使农田免遭流沙的侵袭。', '形容词: securable 副词: securely 比较级: securer 最高级: securest 名词: securement 过去式: secured 过去分词: secured 现在分词: securing 第三人称单数: secures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('galaxy', '[\'ɡæləksi]', 'n.银河；星系；一群杰出的人', '1. The sun is only a very small star in the Galaxy. 太阳只是银河系中一颗很小的恒星。 2. The earth is one of the planets in the Galaxy. 地球是银河系中的星球之一。 3. Each galaxy contains myriads of stars. 每一星系都有无数的恒星。 4. The solar system is a small part of our galaxy. 太阳系是我们星系的一个小部分。', '名词复数: galaxies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('demur', '[dɪ\'mɜːr]', 'v.提出异议；反对；<古>拖延 n.异议；反对', '1. He demurred to my statement. 他对我的陈述提出异议。 2. Lawyer demured what the attestor said. 律师对证人的话的真实性提出了怀疑。 3. Workers demurred at working on Sundays. 工人们反对在星期天工作。 4. I suggested putting the matter to a vote, but the chairman demurred to it. 我建议对此事投票表决，但主席表示反对。 5. He accepted the criticism without demur. 他毫无异议地接受了批评。', '形容词: demurrable 过去式: demurred 过去分词: demurred 现在分词: demurring 第三人称单数: demurs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pole', '[poʊl]', 'n.杆；柱；极点 v.(用杆)支撑 Pole. n.波兰人', '1. Pole vaulters need long run-ups. 撑竿跳需要长距离助跑。 2. The hut was made of poles covered with grass mats. 茅屋用木杆搭成，上面以草席覆盖。 3. He had put up a basket on a pole in the back yard. 他在后院一根柱子上安一个球篮。 4. When Scott reached the South Pole he found Amundsen had anticipated him. 当斯科特抵达南极的时候，发现阿蒙森比他到得更早。', '过去式: poled 过去分词: poled 现在分词: poling 第三人称单数: poles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tariff', '[\'tærɪf]', 'n.关税；价目表 vt.交关税', '1. Tariff barriers crimped the flow of imports. 关税障碍妨碍了进囗货的流入。 2. The government decided to impose a protective tariff on foreign cars. 政府决定对进口汽车征收保护税。 3. A copy of tariff is placed in each room of the hotel. 旅馆的每一个房间都有一份价目表。', '过去式: tariffed 过去分词: tariffed 现在分词: tariffing 第三人称单数: tariffs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tease', '[tiːz]', 'n.揶揄者；戏弄 v.欺负；嘲弄', '1. He is a terrible tease. 他特别爱戏弄人。 2. It\'s too bad of you to tease the child like that. 你那样逗弄小孩真不好。 3. You must never tease a child because he stutters . 你切不可因为一个孩子口吃而去取笑他。 4. Don\'t take it seriously. He\'s only teasing. 别把它当真，他只不过是在开玩笑。', '副词: teasingly 过去式: teased 过去分词: teased 现在分词: teasing 第三人称单数: teases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thrifty', '[\'θrɪfti]', 'adj.节俭的；兴旺的；茁壮的', '1. Her mother is a thrifty housewife. 她妈妈是一个节俭的主妇。 2. Only very thrifty children manage to fill up a money-box. 只有非常节俭的儿童才会设法填满一个储蓄罐。 3. Mr. Thompson is so thrifty that he is able to save more than half of his weekly salary. 汤普森先生是如此节俭,以致他能省下超过一半的周薪。', '副词: thriftily 比较级: triftier 最高级: triftiest 名词: thriftiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('durable', '[\'dʊrəbl]', 'adj.耐用持久的', '1. It\'s very durable. 这很耐久。 2. This pair of shoes is durable. 这双鞋很耐磨。 3. It calls for a durable solution in the area. 在该地区需要一个持久的解决方法。 4. Our products have the quality of being durable. 我们的产品经久耐用。', '副词: durably 名词: durability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resume', '[rɪ\'zuːm]', 'v.重新开始；再继续 n.简历；履历；摘要', '1. We resumed our work after a rest. 休息之后我们重新开始工作。 2. I tried to persuade her to resume her job as secretary. 我试图劝她重新干她的秘书工作。 3. Two days later, they resumed their journey. 两天以後,他们继续旅行。 4. We\'ll stop now and resume at two o\'clock. 我们现在停下来, 到两点再干。 5. I enclosed my resume in my letter. 我在信里附上了我的简历。', '形容词: resumable 名词: resumer 过去式: resumed 过去分词: resumed 现在分词: resuming 第三人称单数: resumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rectangle', '[\'rektæŋɡl]', 'n.长方形；矩形', '1. Rectangle is coming into fashion. 长方形开始流行了。 2. He folded his newspaper into a neat rectangle. 他将报纸折成一个整整齐齐的长方形。 3. A rectangle has four right angles. 一个矩形有四个直角。 4. He drew a rectangle on the blackboard. 他在黑板上画了个矩形。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('drill', '[drɪl]', 'n.钻孔机；钻子；反复操练；播种机 v.练习；钻孔；(军事)训练', '1. The dentist\'s drill made a lot of noise. 牙钻发出很大的噪音。 2. Jack used a drill to bore a hole in the wall above the fireplace. 杰克用钻子在壁炉上方的墙上钻孔。 3. Today\'s art lesson came to an abrupt end when the gongs sounded for a fire drill. 今天的美术课因火灾演习的铃声大作而突然结束。 4. You\'d better set a goal before you start the drill. 练习开始前，你最好设定一个目标。 5. Listen to the first paragraph, then let them drill in teams. 听第一段,然后分组练习。', '名词: driller 过去式: drilled 过去分词: drilled 现在分词: drilling 第三人称单数: drills');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('misgiving', '[ˌmɪs\'ɡɪvɪŋ]', 'n.疑虑；怀疑 动词misgive的现在分词.', '1. All their misgivings were driven out by the arrival of the good news. 一听到这个好消息，他们一切疑虑都烟消云散了。 2. I have many misgivings about taking the job. 我对是否接受那项工作顾虑重重。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('absorbing', '[əb\'sɔːrbɪŋ]', 'adj.吸引人的；非常有趣的 动词absorb的现在分词.', '1. This new novel is an absorbing family saga. 这部新小说是一部引人入胜的家世小说。 2. The novel was so absorbing that she read on without a break even forgetting food and sleep. 这本小说非常引人入胜，她一口气读了下去，甚至废寝忘食。 3. He has a bellyful of absorbing tales. 他有一肚子有趣的故事。 4. Though this novel is very absorbing, its quotations are rather flat. 小说虽然情节很精彩，但引语过于平淡。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('snag', '[snæɡ]', 'n.(隐伏的)障碍；困难；残桩；划破处；抽丝处 v.划破；碰到（暗礁或枯树上）；清除（暗礁等）；迅速抓到', '1. The only snag could be securing a work permit. 唯一的障碍只在于获得一份劳工证。 2. There must be a snag in it somewhere. 一定是在某处出了个小故障. 3. The only snag is that I have no money. 唯一的困难是我没钱。 4. A snag can provide food and a habitat for insects and birds. 残株可以为昆虫和鸟类提供食物和栖息地。 5. Her tights were badly snagged. 她的裤袜划破了一大片。', '形容词: snaggy 过去式: snagged 过去分词: snagged 现在分词: snagging 第三人称单数: snags');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spurt', '[spɜːrt]', 'v.喷出；冲刺 n.喷出；突然一阵；(营业的)突然兴隆；突然高涨', '1. After a silence, Molly let her anger spurt out. 沉默了一会儿，莫莉的怒气便迸发了出来。 2. The wound was spurting blood. 伤口淌著血。 3. The volcano spurted (out) molten lava. 火山喷出了熔岩。 4. The runner spurted as he approached the line. 那赛跑选手在接近终点线时加速冲刺。 5. The water came out with a spurt. 水喷了出来。', '过去式: spurted 过去分词: spurted 现在分词: spurting 第三人称单数: spurts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stash', '[stæʃ]', 'vt.隐藏；储藏 n.隐藏地点；隐藏物', '1. Select the option to stash the password to a file. 选择将密码隐藏在在文件中的选项。 2. And you will have your personal garage to stash your rides. 你将拥有自己的个人修车场以隐藏你的赛车。', '过去式: stashed 过去分词: stashed 现在分词: stashing 第三人称单数: stashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bead', '[biːd]', 'n.珠子；滴 vt.用珍珠布置或覆盖；象珍珠一样串成线 vi.形成珍珠', '1. The hat was decorated with colored beads. 那顶帽子上饰有彩色珠子。 2. Brightly colored bead chaser featured in the middle. 在中间有明亮的彩色珠子。 3. His back was beaded with sweat. 他的背上布满了汗珠。', '过去式: beaded 过去分词: beaded 现在分词: beading 第三人称单数: beads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('riddle', '[\'rɪdl]', 'n.谜；谜语 vt.解谜；出谜题；充满；打洞；筛选 vi.出谜题', '1. That painting is still a riddle to us. 那幅画对我们仍然是个谜。 2. He could not solve the riddle. 他猜不出这个谜。 3. He got the answer to the riddle as quick as a flash. 他一下子就猜中了谜底。 4. The riddle was at last unriddled. 这个谜语终于得到了解答。 5. She loved to riddle out the solution to problems. 她喜欢解答问题。', '名词: riddler 过去式: riddled 过去分词: riddled 现在分词: riddling 第三人称单数: riddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('average', '[\'ævərɪdʒ]', 'n.平均数；平均水平 adj.平均的；一般的；通常的 v.取平均值；达到平均水平', '1. The average of 4,6 and 8 is 6. 4,6, 8的平均数是6。 2. Temperatures are below average for the time of year. 温度低于此时的年平均温度。 3. The average age of the boys in this class is fifteen. 本班男生的平均年龄是十五岁。 4. Tom\'s work at school is above the average. 汤姆的功课是中上等水平。 5. If you average 4, 6 and 11,you get 7 . 如果你将4，6和11平均，你即得7。', '副词: averagely 名词: averageness 过去式: averaged 过去分词: averaged 现在分词: averaging 第三人称单数: averages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eccentric', '[ɪk\'sentrɪk]', 'adj.古怪的；反常的；不同圆心的 n.怪人；[物]偏心轮', '1. The old lady is a bit of an eccentric. 这位老太是个有点古怪的人。 2. She put him down as an eccentric person. 她认为他是个行为古怪的人。 3. His actions since that morning have been eccentric and unpredictable. 自从那天早晨,他的行动一直是反常而不可捉摸。 4. The motors and drive units on these two types of polisher\'s oscillate in an eccentric circular motion. 发动机和转速单位在这两种抛光机上的振蒎是一个偏圆心的运动。 5. He had the name of an eccentric. 他有怪人之称。', '副词: eccentrically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('panel', '[\'pænl]', 'n.嵌板；仪表盘；面板；座谈小组；陪审团 v.嵌镶', '1. The builders set the panel in carefully. 建筑工人把嵌板小心地镶上去。 2. The worker will check functions of instrument panel. 工人将检查仪表盘功能。 3. Solar panels are used to power satellites. 太阳能面板用来给卫星提供动力。 4. The date for the panel discussion is fixed now. 座谈会的日期现已确定。 5. He panelled the wall with wood. 他在墙上镶上木板。', '过去式: paneled/panelled 过去分词: paneled/panelled 现在分词: paneling/panelling 第三人称单数: panels/panels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('declare', '[dɪ\'kler]', 'v.宣布（声明）；申报；声明', '1. I now declare this meeting open. 我现在宣布会议开幕。 2. Britain declared war on Germany in 1914. 英国在1914年向德国宣战。 3. The customs asked me if I had anything to declare. 海关人员问我是否有要报税的东西。 4. Do you have anything to declare, jewelry or cash? 你有没有什么东西要申报?珠宝或现金?', '形容词: declarable 名词: declarer 过去式: declared 过去分词: declared 现在分词: declaring 第三人称单数: declares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('correspondence', '[ˌkɔːrə\'spɑːndəns]', 'n.通信；信件；相符，相似；一致，相当', '1. We have carried on a correspondence for years. 多年来,我们一直互相通信。 2. I\'ve fallen behind with my correspondence. 我积压了许多信没回。 3. I\'ve got through a lot of correspondence today. 今天我处理了一大批信件。 4. As her private secretary he has access to all her correspondence. 他是她的私人秘书，能接触到她所有的信件。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fragmentary', '[\'fræɡmənteri]', 'adj.碎片的；碎块的；碎屑状的；零碎的；不完全的', '1. His knowledge of the subject is fragmentary. 有关这学科他的知识残缺不全。 2. The police only have fragmentary evidence. 警方仅有一些支离破碎的证据。 3. What I heard was very fragmentary. 我只听到一句半句的。 4. The earliest historical evidence of the new states is fragmentary. 关于这个新国家的最早的历史文献是很不完整的。', '副词: fragmentarily 名词: fragmentariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imitate', '[\'ɪmɪteɪt]', 'vt.仿效；仿制；模仿', '1. You should imitate great and good people. 你应仿效伟大善良的人。 2. Teachers provide a model for children to imitate. 教师是孩子们仿效的典范。 3. People imitate diamonds with crystal. 人们用水晶仿造钻石。 4. He can imitate his teacher perfectly. 他能维妙维肖地模仿他的老师。', '名词: imitator 过去式: imitated 过去分词: imitated 现在分词: imitating 第三人称单数: imitates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cataclysm', '[\'kætəklɪzəm]', 'n.大洪水；地震；(社会政治的)大变动', '1. The cataclysm flooded the entire valley. 洪水淹没了整个山谷。 2. A cataclysm caused by the dam breaking. 一场因水坝破裂所造成的大洪水。 3. No cataclysm has desolated the whole world. 没有任何激变曾使整个世界变成荒芜。 4. World War II was a cataclysm for all of Europe. 第二次世界大战对整个欧洲是一大剧变。', '形容词: cataclysmic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('listless', '[\'lɪstləs]', 'adj.无精打采的', '1. Because of the death of his mother he is listless all day. 因为母亲的去世，他整天无精打采的。 2. She was very listless after her illness. 她病后懒洋洋的。 3. People are always listless on summer afternoons. 夏天的午后，人们总是无精打采的。 4. Many people feel listless on rainy days. 许多人碰到下雨天就无精打采。', '副词: listlessly 名词: listlessness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pathology', '[pə\'θɑːlədʒi]', 'n.病理学', '1. Pathology is the study of disease. 病理学是研究疾病的科学。 2. All cases were confirmed as RMAL by postoperative pathology. 所有手术病例，术后病理学诊断均为肾错构瘤。', '名词: pathologist 名词复数: pathologies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('renounce', '[rɪ\'naʊns]', 'v.声明放弃；与...断绝关系', '1. He renounced his claim to the property. 他放弃了对财产的要求。 2. The barrister entirely renounce his right to object to a juror. 这位律师完全放弃了反对陪审团成员的权力。 3. It was painful for him to renounce his son. 宣布与儿子脱离关系对他来说是很痛苦的。 4. He renounced his religion and became a Muslim. 他宣布脱离他原来的宗教而成为了一名穆斯林教徒。', '名词: renouncement 过去式: renounced 过去分词: renounced 现在分词: renouncing 第三人称单数: renounces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('definitive', '[dɪ\'fɪnətɪv]', 'adj.权威性的；明确的；确定的；决定性的 n.限定词', '1. Her book is the definitive work on Milton. 她的书是论述米尔顿的权威著作. 2. She\'s written the definitive history of Vienna. 她写下了权威性的维也纳历史。 3. Clearer fossil may provide a definitive answer. 如果能发现更清晰的化石,那么可能提供明确的答案。 4. There is no definitive answer to this. 没有什么确定的答案。', '副词: definitively 名词: definitiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mercury', '[\'mɜːrkjəri]', 'n.水银；（M~）水星；精神', '1. Mercury is a fluid substance. 水银是流体状之。 2. Mercury weighs more than water by about 14 times. 水银比水重约十三倍。 3. Mercury is too dry and poor in oxygen. 水星上面过于干燥，并且缺乏氧气。 4. He has no mercury in him. 他没有精神。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vulgarity', '[vʌl\'ɡærəti]', 'n.粗俗；粗鄙；卑俗性', '1. She was offended by the vulgarity of their jokes. 他们那些粗俗的笑话使她大为不快。 2. Vulgarity is the ugliest word in our language. 粗俗是我们语言中最丑陋的字眼。 3. Talking loudly on a bus is a sign of vulgarity. 在公共汽车上大声喧哗是一种粗鄙的行为。 4. Vulgarity is a very important ingredient in life. 粗鄙是生活中非常重要的组成部分。', '名词复数: vulgarities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allusion', '[ə\'luːʒn]', 'n.暗指；暗示', '1. I was mentioned in the meeting by an allusion. 我在会议上被暗指。 2. The allusion served as a timely reminder to Darnay. 这暗示即刻提醒了代尔那。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appraise', '[ə\'preɪz]', 'vt.评价；估价；鉴定', '1. They tried to appraise the poet-ry of John Milton. 他们试图评价弥尔顿的诗。 2. It is very high that people appraise to his thesis. 人们对他的论文评价很高。 3. It would be unwise to buy the house before having it appraised. 买房子不事先估价是不明智的。 4. The teacher is appraising the students\' work. 老师正在评定学生的作业。', '形容词: appraisable 名词: appraisement 过去式: appraised 过去分词: appraised 现在分词: appraising 第三人称单数: appraises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legend', '[\'ledʒənd]', 'n.传说；传奇；图例', '1. According to the old legend, Romulus was the founder of Rome. 按照古老的传说，罗穆卢斯是古罗马的建国者。 2. This oriental legend is fascinating. 这个东方传说很吸引人。 3. The little girl is very interested in the old legend of immortal creatures. 小女孩对有关永生的精灵的古老传奇非常感兴趣。 4. He is a legend in his lifetime for his scientific discoveries. 他的科学发现使他一生成为传奇人物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scrupulous', '[\'skruːpjələs]', 'adj.小心谨慎的；细心的；严谨的', '1. However, without the most scrupulous cleanliness, this practice can, in some cases, lead to an infection with hepatitis and other sexually transmitted diseases. 不过，如果没有小心谨慎的清洁，这种习惯在一些情形下可能导致肝炎和其它性传播疾病的感染。 2. Only those scrupulous readers can find this mistake. 只有非常细心的读者才会发现这个错误。', '副词: scrupulously 名词: scrupulosity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fluent', '[\'fluːənt]', 'adj.流利的；流畅的', '1. She speaks fluent and idiomatic French. 她说得一口又流利又地道的法语。 2. She likes him all the better for his fluent spoken English. 正因为他操一口流利的英语，她更爱他。 3. His work is rather fluent and felicitous. 他的作品十分流畅，措辞巧妙。 4. Her fluent movements surprised us. 她那协调优美的动作让我们惊奇。', '副词: fluently 名词: fluency');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('log', '[lɔːɡ]', 'n.原木；圆木；(航海、飞行)日志；(船)计程仪 v.伐木；记入(日志)', '1. They are sawing a log into planks. 他们把原木锯成一块块厚板。 2. My brother is chopping logs for the fire. 我哥哥正在为生火劈柴。 3. A log got in his way as he drove. 一根圆木挡住了他开车的去路。 4. The log twiddled round and round in the river. 那根圆木在河水中转来转去。 5. We\'ll log another section of the area today. 今天我们要砍伐另一部分林区的树木。', '过去式: logged 过去分词: logged 现在分词: logging 第三人称单数: logs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('underlying', '[ˌʌndər\'laɪɪŋ]', 'adj.潜在的；隐含的；在下面的；基本的；<经>优先的 动词underlie的现在分词', '1. This word has its underlying meaning. 这个单词有它潜在的含义。 2. The underlying assumption is that the amount of money available is limited. 隐含的假定是可用的资金有限。 3. We dug down to the underlying rock. 我们往下挖直到碰到了下面的石块。 4. The underlying idea is an appealing one. 基础的概念是一种吸引人的概念。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('equivalent', '[ɪ\'kwɪvələnt]', 'adj.等价的 相等的 n.相等物', '1. Is there a French word that is the exact equivalent of the English word `home\'? 法语中有没有和英语home完全一样的对应词?', '副词: equivalently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eminent', '[\'emɪnənt]', 'adj.著名的；卓越的', '1. Was an eminent landscape poet in ancient China. 是中国古代著名的山水诗作家。 2. Eminent physicists from all over the world came to the United States to celebrate the centennial of Einstein\'s birth. 全世界著名的物理学家来到美国庆祝爱因斯坦诞生一百周年。 3. Churchill was one of the world\'s most eminent statesmen. 邱吉尔是世界上最卓越的政治家之一。 4. Throughout the ages this eminent masterpiece has always held a special place in the hearts of Irish people. 各个时代，这一卓越的杰作都始终在爱尔兰民众的心中占据着一个特殊的位置。', '副词: eminently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('culture', '[\'kʌltʃər]', 'n.栽培；文化；教养 vt.培养，栽培', '1. He has to learn the culture of bees. 他得学养蜂。 2. She has studied the cultures of Oriental countries. 她研究过东方各国的文化。 3. He is a man of little culture. 他没多少文化修养。 4. The culture of the mind is vital. 修心养性是极其重要的。', '过去式: cultured 过去分词: cultured 现在分词: culturing 第三人称单数: cultures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('administration', '[ədˌmɪnɪ\'streɪʃn]', 'n.实施；管理；行政；行政部门；任期', '1. He is responsible for the administration of justice. 他负责赏罚。 2. He works in hospital administration. 他从事医院管理工作. 3. The company developed rapidly under his administration. 在他的管理下，公司发展得很快。 4. Head teachers are more involved in administration than in teaching. 校长的行政工作比教学工作多。', '形容词: administrative 副词: administratively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brighten', '[\'braɪtn]', 'v.使变亮；使生辉；发亮；开颜', '1. The paint will brighten the room. 这种油漆将会使房了变亮。 2. Flowers brighten (up) a room. 房间里有了花显得满室生辉。 3. White paint will brighten the room. 白色油漆会使房间显得明亮。 4. He brightened (up) when he heard the good news. 他听到这个好消息时喜形于色。', '名词: brightener 过去式: brightened 过去分词: brightened 现在分词: brightening 第三人称单数: brightens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cherish', '[\'tʃerɪʃ]', 'vt.珍爱；抱有；抚育', '1. Life is hope, so we should cherish life. 生命就是希望 2. I cherish my independence. 我很珍惜我的自由。 3. I cherish the memory of those happy times. 我把那些美好的时光珍藏在自己的记忆里。 4. A mother cherishes her baby. 母亲疼爱孩子。', '副词: cherishingly 名词: cherisher 过去式: cherished 过去分词: cherished 现在分词: cherishing 第三人称单数: cherishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fluster', '[\'flʌstər]', 'n.慌乱；狼狈；混乱 v.使酩醉；慌张；混乱', '1. People fluster ground leaves ship, the woman went up above all with children Immanuel gives birth to a boat. 人们慌乱地离开轮船，妇女和儿童首先上了救世主生船。', '过去式: flustered 过去分词: flustered 现在分词: flustering 第三人称单数: flusters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accustom', '[ə\'kʌstəm]', 'vt.使习惯', '1. He soon gets accustom to dormitory life and make two or three friend. 他不久就逐渐习惯了宿舍的生活并交了两三个朋友。 2. He had to accustom himself to the cold weather. 他不得不使自己习惯于寒冷的天气。 3. You must accustom yourself to getting up early. 你必须使自己习惯于早起。', '过去式: accustomed 过去分词: accustomed 现在分词: accustoming 第三人称单数: accustoms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tract', '[trækt]', 'n.大片土地；器官系统；[解]道；束 n.小册子', '1. He owns a large tract of forest. 他拥有一大片森林。 2. He took many photos of the wide tracts of desert in North Africa. 他拍了许多关于北非的广大沙漠的照片。 3. Osteoporosis is a late complication of digestive tract disease. 骨质疏松症是消化道疾病的晚期并发症之一。 4. He had an infection in the upper respiratory tract. 他上呼吸道感染。 5. He wrote all the campaign tracts. 这些竞选传单全是他写的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('additive', '[\'ædətɪv]', 'n.添加剂 adj.加添的', '1. Food additive can cause allergies. 食品添加剂可能引起过敏。 2. Glycyrrhizin is a kind of food additive which has a bright future. 甘草素是一种很有发展前途的食品添加剂。 3. We can use the additive property of the integral. 我们可利用积分的可加性。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('motivation', '[ˌməʊtɪ\'veɪʃn]', 'n.动机；动力；刺激；积极性', '1. bend on sth 2. Without direction and motivation, a person would not know what to do. 一个人缺乏方向和动力就不知道该干些什么。 3. The most intrinsic motivation for learning is the child\'s spontaneous interests. 学习的最为内在的刺激是儿童自发的兴趣。 4. They lack the motivation to study. 他们缺乏学习的积极性。', '形容词: motivational 副词: motivationally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acquire', '[ə\'kwaɪər]', 'vt.获得；学到；取得', '1. We should try to acquire good habits. 我们应该努力养成良好的习惯。 2. He will acquire the right to permanent residency here. 他将获得这里的永久居留权。 3. We hope to acquire the knowledge in the happiness. 我们希望在快乐中获得知识。 4. One can never acquire enough experience. 经验是永远学不足的。', '形容词: acquirable 名词: acquirer 过去式: acquired 过去分词: acquired 现在分词: acquiring 第三人称单数: acquires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adjourn', '[ə\'dʒɜːrn]', 'v.(使)延期；中止；换地方', '1. The meeting adjourned till five o\'clock. 会议延至五点召开。 2. The chairman adjourn the meeting for a week. 主席把会议延期一周。 3. The motion to adjourn was carried. 休会的提议通过了。 4. The meeting will adjourn sine die. 这个会议将会无限期休会。', '名词: adjournment 过去式: adjourned 过去分词: adjourned 现在分词: adjourning 第三人称单数: adjourns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recently', '[\'riːsntli]', 'adv.最近', '1. Her books have gained popularity recently. 她的书近来大受欢迎。 2. I guess from his red eyes that he has been working too hard recently. 我从他红红的眼睛猜想,他准是最近工作太辛苦了。 3. We have twenty branches abroad, and we\'ve recently opened a new one in Bangkok. 我们在海外有二十家分公司,最近在曼谷新开了一家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('industrious', '[ɪn\'dʌstriəs]', 'adj.勤劳的；勤奋的', '1. I knew that he was an industrious man. 我知道他是一个勤劳的人。 2. The Chinese are industrious people. 中国人民是一个勤劳的民族。 3. The Chinese are an industrious people. 中国人是个勤奋的民族。 4. And others of them have said that he was an industrious plodder rather than an original thinker. 还有人说斯宾塞是个勤奋的实干家而不是独创性的思想家。', '副词: industriously 名词: industriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intellectual', '[ˌɪntə\'lektʃuəl]', 'n.凭理智做事者；知识分子 adj.智力的；聪明的', '1. He likes to set himself up as an intellectual. 他喜欢自命为知识分子。 2. These views were common among intellectuals. 这些观点在知识分子中很普遍。 3. The argument was too intellectual for me; I couldn\'t follow a word of it. 这场争论对我来说太深奥了，我一点都搞不明白。 4. Chess is a highly intellectual game. 象棋是需用高度智力的运动项目。', '副词: intellectually 名词: intellectuality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stir', '[stɜːr]', 'vt.激起；惹起；搅和 vi.活动；引起；挪动 n.骚乱；感动(激动；愤怒或震动)；搅拌', '1. The story stirred her sympathy. 这故事激起了她的同情心。 2. They tried to stir the peoples of the world into triumphant action. 他们试图激励人民大众的无限热情。 3. The oatmeal lumps if you don\'t stir it well. 如果你不好好搅拌，麦片粥会结块。 4. He didn\'t stir while sitting there. 他坐在那里一动不动。 5. The news caused quite a stir in the village. 那消息在村里引起了一片混乱。', '名词: stirrer 过去式: stirred 过去分词: stirred 现在分词: stirring 第三人称单数: stirs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('athlete', '[\'æθliːt]', 'n.运动员', '1. The athlete is suffering from muscular strain. 这名运动员正受肌肉劳损之苦。 2. She will make a very good athlete. 她将来会成为一名很好的运动员。 3. The athlete has an electrifying burst of speed. 这名运动员具有惊人的爆发速度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('imagist', '[\'ɪmɪdʒɪst]', 'n.意像派者 adj.意象派的', '1. Much subsequent poetry in England was influenced by Imagist lord and practice. 后来的英国诗歌中有许多诗受到了意象主义的箴言和实践的影响。 2. Finally,the prospect of the application of the digital imag... 最后,对图像处理技术在焊缝跟踪中的应用前景作了展望。 3. Ezra Pound is the pioneer of the Imagist Movement in the western world. 艾兹拉·庞德是意象运动的发起人。 4. The three famous imagist principles signaled the invention of a New Poetics. 这三条著名的意象主义原则标志了一种全新诗学的创造。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('majority', '[mə\'dʒɔːrəti]', 'n.大多数；多数；多数党；多数派', '1. The majority of people seem to prefer TV to radio. 多数人喜欢电视胜过广播。 2. Racism is abhorrent to the majority of people. 种族主义是大多数人都憎恨的。 3. The Democrats became the majority in the election. 民主党在这次选举中变成了多数党。 4. The Democrats became the majority in the election. 民主党在这次选举中变成了多数党。', '名词复数: majorities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quota', '[\'kwoʊtə]', 'n.限额；配额；定额；最低票数', '1. Why is my Daily Resultb Quota so sall? 为什么我的每日工作限额那么小？ 2. Calculate the total Sentence Quota of the summary. 计算出摘要应包含的句子的限额。 3. The committee reversed its decision on import quota. 委员会取消了对进口货物的配额的决定。 4. The quota on import cars has been lifted. 对汽车的进口配额已被取消。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outspoken', '[aʊt\'spoʊkən]', 'adj.直言无讳的；坦率的 动词outspeak的过去分词.', '1. He is an outspoken critic of the government. 他是一个直言批评政府的人。 2. His outspoken remarks made him an easy target for the opposition. 他那番直言不讳的言语使他成了反对派的主要抨击对象。 3. Uncle Frank is an outspoken man. 弗朗克叔叔是个坦率的人。 4. My boss is an outspoken critic of my ideas. 我的上司总是对我的想法进行坦率的评论。', '副词: outspokenly 名词: outspokenness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('insolent', '[\'ɪnsələnt]', 'adj.粗野的；无礼的；厚颜的；无耻的', '1. My boss is so rude and insolent that I can\'t do with him. 我的老板是那样的粗野无礼，叫我无法忍受。 2. He was insolent in his manner. 他态度傲慢无礼。 3. It was insolent of them to demand special treatment. 他们要求给予特殊待遇,脸皮真厚。', '副词: insolently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('irrepressible', '[ˌɪrɪ\'presəbl]', 'adj.抑制不住的；难以征服的', '1. He registered irrepressible joy. 他流露出压抑不住的喜悦。', '副词: irrepressibly 名词: irrepressibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('taste', '[teɪst]', 'n.味觉；味道；尝试；品味；爱好 v.品尝；有 ... 味道的；体验', '1. I\'ve got a cold and so I have lost my sense of taste. 我伤风了,尝不出味道。 2. The medicine has a bitter taste. 这药有苦味。 3. She likes her first taste of life in a big city. 她喜欢她对大城市生活的初次体验。 4. She has good taste in clothes. 她对服装有很好的审美眼光。 5. That\'s the best wine I\'ve ever tasted. 那是我喝过的最好的酒', '形容词: tastable 过去式: tasted 过去分词: tasted 现在分词: tasting 第三人称单数: tastes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inflate', '[ɪn\'fleɪt]', 'vt.使膨胀；使得意；使通货膨胀 vi.膨胀', '1. We all started to inflate our balloons and eventually one burst. 我们都开始给气球充气，结果有一个爆掉了。 2. He is inflated with pride. 他趾高气扬。 3. A few bidders inflated the prices on purpose. 几个投标人故意抬高价钱。 4. Clothing has inflated in price. 服装涨价了。', '名词: inflator 过去式: inflated 过去分词: inflated 现在分词: inflating 第三人称单数: inflates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('renew', '[rɪ\'nuː]', 'v.重新开始；更新', '1. The trees renew their foliage every year. 树木每年都重新长出叶子。 2. I must renew the water in the fish-tank. 我一定要给鱼箱重新注满水。 3. It is impossible to renew one\'s youth. 重新恢复青春是不可能的。 4. I shall renew my request for a vote. 我将重新要求投票表决。', '名词: renewer 过去式: renewed 过去分词: renewed 现在分词: renewing 第三人称单数: renews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detect', '[dɪ\'tekt]', 'v.发觉；察觉；探测', '1. Do I detect a tinge of irony? 我觉得这话有点儿像反话吧? 2. If you read between the lines, you can detect his contrived explanation. 在字里行间，你可以看出他牵强的解释。 3. I seemed to detect some anger in his voice. 我似乎在他的声音中听出一些怒气。 4. Small quantities of poison were detected in the dead man\'s stomach. 在死者胃中找到了少量的毒药。', '形容词: detectable 名词: detecter 过去式: detected 过去分词: detected 现在分词: detecting 第三人称单数: detects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('microprocessor', '[ˌmaɪkroʊ\'proʊsesər]', 'n.微处理器', '1. Because of its tiny size, it was dubbed a microprocessor. 因为它的尺寸微小，所以被称为微处理器。 2. The microprocessor on the smart card is there for security. 智能卡上的微处理器是为了确保安全。 3. The engine driving this ongoing revolution is the microprocessor. 驱动这场正在进行的革命的“发动机”是微处理器。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('score', '[skɔː]', 'vt.得分；获胜；刻划；划线；批评；给 ... 谱曲 n.得分；刻痕；二十；乐谱 vi.得分；记分；得胜', '1. Hughes scored two goals before half-time. 休斯在上半场进了两个球. 2. The army continued to score successes in the south. 军队在南方不断取得胜利。 3. They scored the floor-boards by pushing furniture about. 他们推动家具 4. could you please score my name off? 请把我的名字从名单中划掉好吗? 5. I recorded the score in a notebook. 我在笔记本上记下了分数。 6. The home team has yet to score. 主队还没有得分.', '名词: scorer 过去式: scored 过去分词: scored 现在分词: scoring 第三人称单数: scores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('qualify', '[\'kwɑːlɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使具备资格；描述；[语]修饰 vi.取得资格；合格', '1. This test will qualify you to fly an aircraft. 这次考试将使你取得驾驶飞机的资格。 2. His knowledge and skills qualify him for the job. 他的知识和技能使他有资格担任这项工作。 3. Your passport qualifies you to receive free medical treatment. 你所持的护照可使你享有免费医疗。 4. I qualify it as a plot. 我说它是一个阴谋。 5. I won\'t qualify until next year. 我明年才具备资格。', '过去式: qualified 过去分词: qualified 现在分词: qualifying 第三人称单数: qualifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laurel', '[\'lɔːrəl]', 'n.月桂树；荣誉 v.戴桂冠；授予荣誉', '1. The display was wreathed in/with laurel. 展品周围环绕着月桂树叶. 2. He had to pose wearing a laurel wreath. 他得摆好戴著月桂花冠的姿势。 3. All other laurels wither before hers. 所有荣誉和她获得的相比都黯然失色。 4. The winner received a laurel crown. 胜利者获得一桂冠。', '过去式: laureled/laurelled 过去分词: laureled/laurelled 现在分词: laureling/laurelling 第三人称单数: laurels/laurels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dilute', '[daɪ\'luːt]', 'vt.稀释；冲淡 adj.冲淡的；稀释的', '1. Dilute the bleach in a gallon of water. 用一加仑水稀释漂白粉。 2. The fragrances are highly diluted. 芳香剂被高度稀释了。 3. The nurse diluted the drug with saline water. 护士用生理盐水把药加以稀释。 4. He thought Rear Admiral Henry\'s presence might dilute the tension of the dinner. 他认为亨利少将的参加也许可以冲淡这顿晚餐的紧张气氛。 5. Readers feel dilute after reading Wei Yingwu\'s poetry, in reality, the poet concealed his solitude under this kind dilute style. 韦应物诗歌给人以冲淡的感觉，其实在这种冲淡的风格下隐含着诗人性格的孤独因素。', '形容词: dilutive 名词: diluter 过去式: diluted 过去分词: diluted 现在分词: diluting 第三人称单数: dilutes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aspire', '[ə\'spaɪər]', 'v.热望；立志', '1. Do you aspire to know the heights, and depths, and lengths, and breadths? 你是否热望要知道上帝的长阔高深？ 2. And thousands of young players aspire to be like him. 千千万万的年轻球手立志要想成为象他那样的英雄。 3. Woman should not only aspire to be educated but also persue independence. 女性不仅应该立志接受教育，还应该追求独立。', '副词: aspiringly 名词: aspirer 过去式: aspired 过去分词: aspired 现在分词: aspiring 第三人称单数: aspires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('craft', '[kræft]', 'n.工艺；手艺；狡诈；船舶；航空器；行会成员 vt.手工制作；精心制作', '1. He graduated from a school of crafts and arts. 他毕业于一所工艺美术学校。 2. He learned his craft from an old master. 他从一位老匠人那儿学得他的手艺。 3. By crafts the gambler tricked them out of all their money. 那个赌徒用诡计赢去了他们所有的钱。 4. Hundreds of small craft accompany the liner into harbour. 数百只小艇随同这艘班轮驶入港湾。 5. He told us a carefully crafted story. 他给我们讲了一个精心编织的故事。', '名词: crafter 过去式: crafted 过去分词: crafted 现在分词: crafting 第三人称单数: crafts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('episode', '[\'epɪsoʊd]', 'n.一段情节；片段；轶事；插曲', '1. The first episode goes out next Friday evening at 8.00 pm. 下星期五晚上8时播出第一集。 2. Relating to or resembling an episode. 插曲似的关于或类似插曲的 3. One of the funniest episodes in the book occurs in chapter 6. 书中最有趣的情节是在第6章。 4. The episode of this film sounds good. 这部电影的插曲很好听。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rust', '[rʌst]', 'n.铁锈；锈菌；赤褐色 vi.生锈；变成锈色 vt.使 ... 生锈；损害', '1. The tools will corrode with rust if never used. 这些工具如长期不用会长铁锈而损坏。 2. Rust is eating away the iron hinge. 铁锈正腐蚀着铁铰链。 3. The pipes had clogged with rust. 铁锈阻塞了管道。 4. How can I remove the rust from the iron door? 我怎样才能把铁门上的锈除掉呢？ 5. Iron exposed to damp air will rust. 放在空气潮湿地方的铁会生锈。 6. The rain will rust the iron roof. 雨水将使铁皮屋顶生锈。', '形容词: rustable 过去式: rusted 过去分词: rusted 现在分词: rusting 第三人称单数: rusts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coin', '[kɔɪn]', 'n.硬币；金钱 vt.铸造（钱币）；创造（新词） adj.硬币的；投币的', '1. He put a coin into the insertion slot. 他往投币孔投入一枚硬币。 2. He paid me in coin. 他付给我的都是硬币。 3. Father dug up an old coin in the garden. 父亲在花园里掘出一枚古钱币。 4. They were granted the right to coin money. 他们获得铸造钱币的授权。 5. The reverse of the coin was stamped with an eagle. 硬币的反面压印的是一只鹰。', '形容词: coinable 名词: coiner 过去式: coined 过去分词: coined 现在分词: coining 第三人称单数: coins');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('employer', '[ɪm\'plɔɪər]', 'n.雇主', '1. He sued his employer for wrongful dismissal. 他控告雇主非法解雇他。 2. The university is a major employer in the area. 该大学是这一地区的大雇主。 3. He was in his employer\'s good graces. 他深得雇主的赏识。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attain', '[ə\'teɪn]', 'v.实现；获得；达到', '1. We can attain whatever goal we set in our mind. 我们设定了什么目标，就能实现什么目标。 2. We should be able to attain that goal. 我们应该能够实现这个目标。 3. The country attained its independence in 1972. 这个国家在1972年获得了独立。 4. They\'re sure to attain emancipation in the end. 他们最后一定能获得解放。', '形容词: attainable 名词: attainability 过去式: attained 过去分词: attained 现在分词: attaining 第三人称单数: attains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pine', '[paɪn]', 'n.松树；松木 vi.消瘦；渴望', '1. The pine trees defy severe cold. 松树不畏严寒。 2. It\'s a noted place for its pine tree and springs. 这是一个以松树和泉水著称的地方。 3. There is a pine forest near our house. 我们家附近有片松树林。 4. Pine is a soft wood and teak is a hard wood. 松木是软木，柚木是硬木。 5. He pined away after his daughter died. 他的女儿死后，他逐渐变得憔悴了。', '过去式: pined 过去分词: pined 现在分词: pining 第三人称单数: pines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('capable', '[\'keɪpəbl]', 'adj.有能力的；能干的；有...的可能性', '1. Not everyone is capable of judging art. 并不是每个人都有鉴赏艺 术的能力。 2. Only human beings are capable of speech. 只有人类才具有说话的能力。 3. Bill is rated as very capable. 大家公认比尔很能干。 4. He is a very capable administrator. 他是个十分能干的行政人员。', '副词: capably 名词: capableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('completion', '[kəm\'pliːʃn]', 'n.完成；结束', '1. The job is at last nearing completion. 这项工作终于快要完成了。 2. You may move into the house on completion. 办完手续后，你就可以搬进去。 3. The film is on the point of completion. 电影制作即将完成。 4. The road is nearing completion . 那条路快完成了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fault', '[fɔːlt]', 'n.缺点；故障；过错；[地]断层 v.找 ... 错误', '1. I like him despite his faults. 虽然他有很多缺点，我仍然喜欢他。 2. He has many faults, but vanity is not one of them. 他有很多缺点，但并没有虚荣心。 3. There is a fault in the electrical system. 电路系统出了故障。 4. It was not our fault that we were late. 这次迟到不是我们的错。 5. No one could fault his performance. 他的演出无懈可击.', '过去式: faulted 过去分词: faulted 现在分词: faulting 第三人称单数: faults');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dairy', '[\'deri]', 'n.牛奶场；乳品店；乳制品；地方小店 adj.牛奶的；乳制品的', '1. Milk, butter and cheese are brought in here from dairy farms . 牛奶、奶油、奶酪从牛奶场运到这里。 2. With the newly-imported equipment, the dairy can upgrade their milk to the required standard. 有了新进口的设备，乳品厂可以使新生产的牛奶达到要求。 3. The yogurt sold by this dairy is delicious. 这家乳品店出售的酸奶非常好喝。 4. Go and buy me some cleese at the dairy. 去乳品店帮我买些奶酷。 5. The dairy cattle are going to come in. 奶牛要产仔了。', '名词复数: dairies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grimly', '[ɡrɪmli]', 'adv.严格地；冷酷地；可怕地', '1. I admire him for his grim courage. 我佩服他的坚韧不拔的勇气。 2. She stuck to her task like grim death. 她百折不挠地执行任务。 3. We had a grim struggle before we won. 我们经历了一场恶斗才赢得胜利。 4. He held on to the branch like grim death. 他紧紧抓住树枝不松手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transfix', '[træns\'fɪks]', 'vt.刺穿；钉住；使呆住', '1. He transfixed the enemy\'s heart with a spear. 他用长矛刺穿了敌人的心脏。 2. She stood transfixed with fear. 她因恐惧而呆立不动。 3. He stood staring at the ghost, transfixed with terror. 他站在那里看着那个鬼', '名词: transfixion 过去式: transfixed 过去分词: transfixed 现在分词: transfixing 第三人称单数: transfixes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exasperate', '[ɪɡ\'zæspəreɪt]', 'v.使 ... 恼怒；激怒；使恶化 adj.被激怒的；表面粗糙的', '1. That child exasperates me. 那孩子真让我生气。 2. She was exasperated at his stupidity. 她因为他的愚笨而发怒。 3. He shouted in an exasperate voice. 他以愤怒的声音嚷着。', '副词: exasperatedly 名词: exasperater 过去式: exasperated 过去分词: exasperated 现在分词: exasperating 第三人称单数: exasperates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('Jupiter', '[\'dʒuːpɪtər]', 'n.木星；[罗神]朱庇特', '1. How many moons does Jupiter have? 木星有多少卫星? 2. Jupiter is unlike the Earth in almost every way. 木星与地球几乎完全不同。 3. Jupiter is one of the sun\'s planets. 木星是太阳的一个行星。 4. Jupiter appeared in the likeness of a swan. 朱庇特主神看上去象只天鹅。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impermeable', '[ɪm\'pɜːrmiəbl]', 'adj.不能渗透的；不渗透性的', '1. Water cannot easily flow in these impermeable rocks. 水不容易流进那些不透水的岩石。 2. Thin layers of other impermeable materials are found in nature, too. 在自然界中也发现有其他非渗透性薄层物质。', '副词: impermeably 名词: impermeability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overseas', '[ˌoʊvər\'siːz]', 'adj.海外的 adv.在海外', '1. The overseas trade has become the main project. 海外贸易成为主要的项目。 2. She is an overseas student in Britain. 她是个在英国的外国留学生。 3. Over the years, hundreds of overseas students have studied at that university. 几年来，几百个留学生在那所大学学习过。 4. He lived overseas for many years. 他在海外生活了多年。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('banish', '[\'bænɪʃ]', 'vt.驱逐；流放；消除', '1. His lies caused his wife to banish him from the house. 他因说谎而被老婆驱逐出家门。 2. The sound of doctrine rings out daily in order to banish various curiosities about this world. 一种主义的声响日以夜继，千日不绝，用以驱逐人们对这个世界的种种好奇与揣测！ 3. You can banish that idea from your mind. 你能消除心中的那种念头。 4. The doctor advised her to banish fear and anxiety. 医生劝她消除恐惧和忧虑。', '名词: banisher 过去式: banished 过去分词: banished 现在分词: banishing 第三人称单数: banishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devoted', '[dɪ\'voʊtɪd]', 'adj.投入的；深爱的；全心全意的 动词devote的过去式和过去分词.', '1. He lived a life devoted entirely to sensual pleasure. 他一生耽于肉欲。 2. He is very devoted to our cause. 他非常忠实于我们的目标。 3. She was devoted to her mother and looked after her for many years. 她深爱着她的母亲并照顾了她很多年。 4. It is in being humble that our love becomes real, devoted and ardent. 因着谦卑我们的爱才变得真实，投入和充满热情。 5. He devoted himself entirely to music. 他将一生奉献给了音乐。', '副词: devotedly 名词: devotedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('balcony', '[\'bælkəni]', 'n.阳台；楼座；包厢', '1. The prospect from the balcony was breathtaking. 从阳台上看去景色美极了。 2. He planted some flowers on the balcony that projects over the street. 他在那个伸出到街上的阳台上种了些花。 3. He was watching a performance from the balcony. 他正在从楼厅上看电影。 4. I\'m sorry, all the balcony seats are sold out. 抱歉,包厢的票都卖完了。', '名词复数: balconies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('zealous', '[\'zeləs]', 'adj.热心的；狂热的；热衷的', '1. He is ticketed as a zealous reformer. 他被描述成一个热心的改革家。 2. The zealous dealer has an ideal idea of dealing with the meal. 热心的商人有一个处理膳食的理想主意。 3. Her beauty drew many zealous suitors. 她的美丽引来了无数狂热的求婚者。 4. This zealous order hunts Arthas\'s servants, the undead, with a frightening ruthlessness that demonstrates their determination to fix past mistakes. 这个狂热的组织以令人恐惧的残酷猎杀着阿尔萨斯的不死仆从，以此证明他们修正对过去错误的决心。', '副词: zealously 名词: zealousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('senior', '[\'siːniər]', 'adj.地位较高的；高级的；年长的；资深的 n.上司；年长者；长辈；大四学生', '1. He is senior to me, though he is younger. 他地位比我高，虽然他比我年轻。 2. She was unfit for such a senior position. 她不能胜任这样的高级职位。 3. Lying north of the church is a girls\' senior high school. 位于这座教堂以北的是一所女子高中。 4. Although he is senior to his wife, he is inferior to her in salary. 虽然她年长于他的妻子,但他妻子的收入比他高。 5. The three vice-ministers are my seniors. 三位副部长都是我的上司。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('integral', '[\'ɪntɪɡrəl]', 'adj.完整的；构成整体所必需的 n.[数] 积分；完整', '1. The transit line is an integral transportation link for the 2010 Winter Olympics. 该隧道是温哥华为2010年冬季奥运会打造的一条完整地下线路。 2. The kitchen is an integral part of a house. 厨房是房子不可缺的部分 3. These policies form an integral whole. 这是很完整的。 4. The bodies of the carts were integral, that is made of one moulding. 马车的车身是完整的，而且是根据同一个模型做出来的。', '副词: integrally 名词: integrality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immature', '[ˌɪmə\'tʃʊr]', 'adj.不成熟的', '1. His immature behavior was not so interesting. 他的不成熟的表现看上去不那么有趣。 2. Sows are immature for the majority of their breeding life. 母猪在它大部分繁殖过程是不成熟的。', '副词: immaturely 名词: immaturity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mitigate', '[\'mɪtɪɡeɪt]', 'vt.减轻；缓和', '1. The judge said that nothing could mitigate the cruelty with which the stepmother had treated the girl. 法官说没有任何理由可以把那个继母残忍虐待女孩的罪责减轻。 2. Her words mitigated my suffering. 她的话减轻了我的痛苦。 3. The government is trying to mitigate the effects of inflation. 政府正试图缓和通货膨胀的影响。', '形容词: mitigable 名词: mitigation 过去式: mitigated 过去分词: mitigated 现在分词: mitigating 第三人称单数: mitigates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acquit', '[ə\'kwɪt]', 'v.宣布无罪；开释；原谅；表现', '1. He was acquitted of the crime. 他被宣告无罪。 2. They tried to bribe the judge to acquit them. 他们试图贿赂法官判他们无罪。 3. Will the court acquit him of the crime? 法庭会宣判他无罪释放吗? 4. I acquit Edward of all essential misconduct. 我原谅爱德华的所有根本过错。', '名词: acquitter 过去式: acquitted 过去分词: acquitted 现在分词: acquitting 第三人称单数: acquits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mason', '[\'meɪsn]', 'n.石匠；泥瓦匠 Mason. n.梅森(人名)；共济会会员', '1. He asked the mason to make him a tombstone. 他要求这个石匠给他做一块墓碑。 2. He carved marble faster than any mason. 他雕刻大理石的速度比任何石匠都快。 3. The mason flushed the joint with mortar. 泥工用灰浆把接缝处嵌平。', '过去式: masoned 过去分词: masoned 现在分词: masoning 第三人称单数: masons');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abortive', '[ə\'bɔːrtɪv]', 'adj.失败的；流产的；发育不全的', '1. We had to abandon our abortive attempts. 我们的尝试没有成功，不得不放弃。 2. Somehow the whole abortive affair got into the FBI files. 这件早已夭折的案子不知怎么就进了联邦调查局的档案。 3. All efforts to trace and locate her next of kin proved abortive. 一切追查并找到其亲属的努力证明流产了。 4. Even an abortive attempt is better than a failed strategy. 即使是不成熟的尝试，也胜于胎死腹中的策略。', '副词: abortively 名词: abortiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('harass', '[\'hærəs]', 'vt.使疲乏；骚扰', '1. The Mongols would harass the enemy from the sides until the latter were exhausted, then close in for the kill. 蒙古军会从四面八方不断侵扰敌人，直到敌人筋疲力尽，再包围并一举歼灭。 2. They received the order to harass the enemy\'s rear. 他们接到骚扰敌人后方的命令。 3. The guerrillas lay up by day, and by night sallied out to harass the enemy. 游击队员们白天隐藏起来，夜晚进行出击，骚扰敌人。', '名词: harasser 过去式: harassed 过去分词: harassed 现在分词: harassing 第三人称单数: harasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exorbitant', '[ɪɡ\'zɔːrbɪtənt]', 'adj.(价格等)过高的；过分的；不合法的', '1. The price of food here is exorbitant. 这儿的食物价格太高。 2. That hotel charges exorbitant prices. 那家旅馆漫天要价。 3. You should be sensible and not make exorbitant demands. 你应该通情达理，不要作过分的要求。', '副词: exorbitantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blend', '[blend]', 'v.混合 n.混合物', '1. Oil does not blend with water. 油不溶於水。 2. The sea and the sky seemed to blend into each another. 大海和蓝天似乎连成了一片。 3. The poem blends the separate ingredients into a unity. 这首诗把几个分开的部分融合为一体。 4. The curtains blend in perfectly with the furniture. 窗帘(的颜色)跟家具(的颜色)十分和谐。 5. Which blend of coffee would you like? 你要哪一种混合咖啡?', '过去式: blended/blent 过去分词: blended/blent 现在分词: blending 第三人称单数: blends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reform', '[rɪ\'fɔːrm]', 'n.改革；改良 v.改革；革新；改造', '1. Our reform made an inexorable march of progress. 我们的改革取得了势不可挡的进展。 2. Many reforms must be made to the education system. 教育体制要作许多改革。 3. The reform and open policy has Brought us Chinese people a rich and colourful life. 改革开放的政策给我们中国人民带来了富裕和多彩的生活。 4. He intends to make several reforms in the prison system. 他打算在监狱制度方面实行一些改良。 5. A new leader will reform the unjust system. 新的领导人将改革不当的制度。', '形容词: reformable 名词: reformability 过去式: reformed 过去分词: reformed 现在分词: reforming 第三人称单数: reforms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('detriment', '[\'detrɪmənt]', 'n.损伤；损害物', '1. He works long hours to the detriment of his health. 他长时间的工作，有损健康。 2. This tax can not be introduced without detriment to the economy. 这一税收制度一旦施行，必定会危害国民经济。 3. Smoking is now considered a detriment to good health. 现在认为,烟对健康有害。 4. His lack of education is a serious detriment to his career. 他的未受教育对他的事业是一种严重的妨碍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('faucet', '[\'fɔːsɪt]', 'n.水龙头', '1. The water from the faucet was cloudy. 水龙头里流出的水很混浊。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('asset', '[\'æset]', 'n.资产；优点；有用的东西', '1. It was too early to conclude if there was an asset price bubble. 在现阶段下结论,认为出现资产价格泡沫属言之尚早。 2. Private consumption improved and asset prices rose sharply. 私人消费有所改善,资产价格更大幅攀升。 3. The tennis player\'s speed is his great asset. 那个网球运动员动作迅速，这是他的一大优势。 4. A sense of humour is a great asset for a person. 幽默感是一个人的宝贵资产。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eject', '[i\'dʒekt]', 'v.喷射；放逐；驱逐', '1. When endangered,octopuses eject an inky substance,which is used as a screen. 遇到危险的时候，章鱼能够喷射一种墨水状的液体，掩蔽它们逃走。 2. When triggered,these cells eject poison-tipped barbs that help the jellyfish catch food in the ocean. 当受到触发时，这些细胞喷射出有助于海蜇在海洋中捕捉食物的有毒倒钩。 3. If the voters go further and eject Mr Harper, that, sadly, will not be because they have been convinced by the cerebral Mr Dion\'s worthy carbon tax. 如果选民进一步驱逐哈珀，遗憾的是，这不会发生，因为他们在脑海里确信狄恩应得烟尘排放税。 4. He says Pyongyang\'s recent moves to eject international inspectors and resume activity at its main nuclear reactor have dealt a serious blow to the process. 他说，平壤最近驱逐国际核查人员以及恢复其主要核反应堆的作法都对和谈进程造成了严重的打击。', '形容词: ejectable 过去式: ejected 过去分词: ejected 现在分词: ejecting 第三人称单数: ejects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circuit', '[\'sɜːrkɪt]', 'n.巡回；线路；环形；电路；回路 v.巡回；绕 ... 环形', '1. For many years he was top banana on the circuit. 几年来,他是巡回剧团里的主角。 2. The commanding officer made a circuit of the camp. 指挥官在营地巡视一周。 3. Complete minor repairs to circuit wiring. 完成线路小修。 4. The circuit is a conventional ring counter. 此线路是一个普通的环形计数器。 5. I hit the lunch-and-lecture circuit again. 我又去参加那些巡回午餐演讲了。', '过去式: circuited 过去分词: circuited 现在分词: circuiting 第三人称单数: circuits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exacting', '[ɪɡ\'zæktɪŋ]', 'adj.严格的；吃力的 动词exact的现在分词形式.', '1. If the government goes on exacting so much from the taxpayer, it will not last long. 如果该政府继续如此征税的话，它将不会持续多久。 2. I have so trained myself in secretarial work that only exacting problems are interesting to me. 毫不夸张的说，我在文秘方面受过严密的训练，越是难度大的工作越能激起我的工作热情。 3. His work was so exacting that by the end of the day he was worn out. 他的工作十分吃力,到一天过完的时候他已经精疲力竭了。', '副词: exactingly 名词: exactingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complicated', '[\'kɑːmplɪkeɪtɪd]', 'adj.复杂难懂的；结构复杂的 动词complicate的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The novel is too complicated for your age. 这小说就你的年龄来说太复杂了。 2. The tax laws are so complicated that only an expert can provide enlightenment. 税务法非常复杂，只有专家才能解释清楚。 3. Obtaining a refund from the company is a complicated procedure. 向公司索取退款手续很复杂。 4. An automobile is a complicated apparatus. 汽车是台复杂的机器.', '副词: complicatedly 名词: complicatedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('survey', '[\'sɜːrveɪ]', 'n.问卷；测量；调查；纵览；视察 v.调查；审视；研究；测量；勘定；环视', '1. A recent survey of public opinions shows that most people are worried about the increasing crime. 一份最近的民意调查表明,大多数人对不断增长的犯罪率表示忧虑。 2. The surveyor made a survey of the land. 测量员对土地进行了测量。 3. After much delay, the results of the survey were published. 耽搁多时之后,调查结果终于公布了。 4. From the top of the hill you can have a survey of the whole city. 从山顶上你可以俯瞰整个城市。 5. They surveyed the damage inflicted by the storm. 他们调查了暴风雨造成的损失。', '名词: surveyor 名词复数: surveys 过去式: surveyed 过去分词: surveyed 现在分词: surveying 第三人称单数: surveys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transplant', '[\'trænsplænt]', 'v.移居；移栽(植物)；移植(器官) n.移植；移植物', '1. The villagers will transplant to another place. 村民们将移居到另外一个地方。 2. The peasants bent over to transplant rice seedlings in the fields. 农民们在地里弯腰插秧。 3. It is now possible to transplant organs from animals into people. 现在将动物身上的器官移植入人体内已经成为了可能。 4. The doctors will transplant a human heart into the patient. 医生们将把一颗人的心脏移植到这个病人身上。 5. I think the heart transplant is a wonderful thing. 我认为心脏移植是件神奇的事。', '形容词: transplantable 名词: transplantation 过去式: transplanted 过去分词: transplanted 现在分词: transplanting 第三人称单数: transplants');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reverse', '[rɪ\'vɜːrs]', 'v.逆转；倒退；互换；改变 adj.相反的；反面的；颠倒的 n.相反；背面；失败；倒档', '1. The government has failed to reverse the economic decline. 政府未能扭转经济滑坡的趋势。 2. He reversed the car into a tree. 他倒车撞到了树上。 3. Statistics showed a reverse trend to that recorded in other countries. 统计数字表明这种趋向与其他国家所示情况迥异。 4. Count down in reverse order 10, 9, 8... 倒数--10、 9、 8... 5. In hot weather, the reverse happens. 在热天,情况相反。', '副词: reversely 名词: reverser 过去式: reversed 过去分词: reversed 现在分词: reversing 第三人称单数: reverses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('poultry', '[\'poʊltri]', 'n.家禽；家禽肉', '1. The poultry are being fed. 家禽正在吃饲料。 2. The farm breeds a wide range of poultry. 这个农场饲养各种家禽。 3. Poultry is rather cheap now. 现在的禽肉相当便宜。 4. There is not much poultry in the shops. 商店里禽肉不太多。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('transition', '[træn\'zɪʃn]', 'n.转变；过渡', '1. Such a sudden transition must affect her. 这样的一个突然变化一定会影响她。 2. His attitude underwent an abrupt transition. 他的态度突然改变了。 3. We hope there will be a peaceful transition to the new system. 我们希望能够和平过渡到新的制度。', '形容词: transitional 副词: transitionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aged', '[eɪdʒd]', 'adj.年老的 动词age的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. She nurses her aged mother. 她照顾年迈的母亲。 2. Aged people are always envious of young people\'s energy. 上年纪的人总羡慕年轻人的精力。', '副词: agedly 名词: agedness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invocation', '[ˌɪnvə\'keɪʃn]', 'n.祈祷；乞灵；（法律的）实施；[计]调用', '1. A warlock can use this invocation to dispel magic. 一个邪术师可以使用这个能力来解除法术。', '形容词: invocational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('destiny', '[\'destəni]', 'n.命运', '1. Destiny is sometimes cruel. 命运有时是残酷的。 2. Your destiny is interwoven with mine. 你的命运已和我的命运结合在一起了。 3. Some people believe that the Fates preside over man\'s destiny. 有些人相信，命运之神支配人类的命运。', '名词复数: destinies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('community', '[kə\'mjuːnəti]', 'n.社区；社会；公众；共同体；团体；共享；共有；[生]群落', '1. Here is a local Jewish community. 这是当地犹太人的一个社区。 2. Everyone should invest some time in community service. 每个人都应该花些时间在社区服务上。 3. Community colleges have become popular and their enrollments have increased rapidly. 社区大学日渐增多，报名人数迅速增长。 4. The international community forbids use of any chemical weapons. 国际社会禁止使用一切化学武器。', '名词复数: communities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prodigious', '[prə\'dɪdʒəs]', 'adj.巨大的；惊人的；奇异的', '1. A nuclear reactor generates prodigious amounts of heat. 一座核反应堆能发出巨大的热量。 2. We are all overwhelmed by his prodigious memory. 我们都被他那惊人的记忆力折服了。 3. The Sussex ironworks were carried on at such a prodigious expense of wood. 苏塞克斯铁厂象这样办下去使木材造成如此惊人的耗费。 4. She was shocked by the prodigious view. 她对这奇异的景象感到震惊。', '副词: prodigiously 名词: prodigiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revoke', '[rɪ\'voʊk]', 'vt.撤回，取消，废除 vi.藏牌，有牌不跟 n.藏牌', '1. We hereby revoke the agreement of May8, 2004. 我方特此宣告于2004年5月8日签订的合同无效。 2. His driving licence was revoked after the crash. 他撞车后驾驶执照被吊销了。 3. The intention to revoke a will. 将遗嘱取消的打算。', '名词: revoker 过去式: revoked 过去分词: revoked 现在分词: revoking 第三人称单数: revokes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abashed', '[ə\'bæʃt]', 'adj.羞愧的；局促不安的 动词abash的过去式和过去分词.', '1. I stood abashed at his rebuke. 面对他的斥责我感到无地自容。 2. The girl felt abashed at the sight of the room filled with strangers. 女孩因房中挤满陌生人而局促不安。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('efface', '[ɪ\'feɪs]', 'v.擦掉；抹去；使（自己）不受人注意；忘却', '1. He would have to efface himself before his visitors. 他每每只好在客人面前躲而避之。 2. Time alone will efface those unpleasant memories. 只有时间才能使人淡忘那些不快的记忆。 3. Time and weather had long ago effaced the inscription on the monument. 岁月和风雨早已磨掉纪念碑上的铭文。', '形容词: effaceable 名词: effacement 过去式: effaced 过去分词: effaced 现在分词: effacing 第三人称单数: effaces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proceed', '[proʊ\'siːd]', 'vi.继续进行；开始；着手', '1. We received sanction to proceed with our plans. 我们获准继续进行我们的计划。 2. Please go upstairs and proceed through the security check and immigration. 请您到楼上继续进行安全检查和移民检查。 3. Please proceed with your presentation. 请开始你的简报。 4. After everyone was seated the chairman proceeded to announce his plan. 大家就坐后，主席开始宣布他的计划。', '名词: proceeder 过去式: proceeded 过去分词: proceeded 现在分词: proceeding 第三人称单数: proceeds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('board', '[bɔːrd]', 'n.木板；布告板；董事会；船舷或机舱；伙食；舞台 v.登(飞机、车、船等)；接受乘客；有偿提供食宿；搭伙；用木板覆盖', '1. Will you draw the nails from this board? 请你把钉子从这块木板上拔出来好吗? 2. Paste down the map on the board. 把这张地图用浆糊贴在布告板上。 3. Her election to the board of directors caused great surprise. 她被选进董事会,令人大为吃惊。 4. Please get on board at once; the plane is taking off very soon. 请即刻登机；飞机马上就要起飞了。 5. Passengers must board the ship by 6 p.m. 旅客必须在下午六点钟以前上船。', '过去式: boarded 过去分词: boarded 现在分词: boarding 第三人称单数: boards');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('emphatic', '[ɪm\'fætɪk]', 'adj.强调的；(人)明确表示的；有目共睹的；[语]语势强的', '1. \"You must go\", she said in an emphatic tone. “你非得去不可”,她用强调的口气说。 2. He refused my offer with an emphatic shake of head. 他用力摇了摇头，拒绝了我的提议。 3. He was emphatic that he could not work with her. 他强调他不能与她共事。 4. He was emphatic about the importance of being punctual. 他强调严守时间的重要性。', '副词: emphatically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cell', '[sel]', 'n.单人牢房；小房间；细胞；蜂房的巢室；电池；政治小组；(计算机电子表格的)单元格；<美口>手机', '1. The prisoner was locked in a cell. 那囚犯被关在单人牢房内。 2. She was found prostrate on the floor of the cell. 有人发现她趴在小屋的地板上。 3. The cancer cell may invade other parts of the body. 癌细胞可能侵袭身体的其他部分。 4. There is a queen bee in the cell. 蜂房里有一只蜂王。', '过去式: celled 过去分词: celled 现在分词: celling 第三人称单数: cells');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sallow', '[\'sæloʊ]', 'adj.灰黄色的；气色不好的 v.使发黄 n.柳树', '1. She is ill with a sallow face. 她病了，面色发黄。', '副词: sallowly 比较级: sallower 最高级: sallowest 名词: sallowness 过去式: sallowed 过去分词: sallowed 现在分词: sallowing 第三人称单数: sallows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('casual', '[\'kæʒuəl]', 'adj.非正式的；漫不经心的；偶然的；临时的；休闲的 n.便装；临时工', '1. He was wearing casual clothes. 他穿着便服。 2. The plan grew out of a casual conversation. 这个计划出自于一次非正式的谈话。 3. He sidled past, trying to seem casual. 他悄悄地溜了过去,竭力装作漫不经心的样子。 4. She is casual about winning the prize. 她对获奖漫不经心。', '副词: casually 名词: casualness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crippling', '[\'krɪplɪŋ]', 'adj.严重损害身体的；造成严重后果的 动词cripple的现在分词形式.', '1. The young leader was in full flower when he was struck down by a crippling disease. 这个年轻的领导人正值其事业到达顶峰之时，被一种致人残废的病症折磨倒了。 2. Strikes were as crippling as taxes. 罢工如同重税一样造成损害。 3. The high unemployment rate has a crippling effect on the economy. 高失业率对于经济造成严重影响。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('limp', '[lɪmp]', 'n.跛行 adj.柔软的；无力的；软弱的 vi.跛行；蹒跚', '1. Two weeks later, the dog could walk with a limp. 两周后，狗儿可以跛行了。 2. The injury left him with a permanent limp. 他受伤后就一直瘸了。 3. This young man is wearing a limp grey sweater. 这个年轻人穿着一件柔软的灰色运动衫。 4. The man\'s shrieked whistle struck his limp ears. 男人尖细的口哨声传到它那柔软的耳朵里。 5. He that lives with cripples learns to limp. 近朱者赤，近墨者黑。', '副词: limply 比较级: limper 最高级: limpest 名词: limpness 过去式: limped 过去分词: limped 现在分词: limping 第三人称单数: limps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trash', '[træʃ]', 'n.废物；垃圾 vt.废弃；捣毁；擦去 vi.捣毁', '1. The doctors eliminated trash from his body. 医生们帮他排除体内废物。 2. I no longer consider people on welfare white trash. 我不再认为靠福利救济的人是白人当中的废物。 3. Please take the trash to the garbage can. 请将垃圾拿到垃圾筒去。 4. People shouldn\'t dump trash on public land. 人们不应在公共场所倾倒垃圾。 5. Trash that old thing and buy a new one. 扔掉老的再买一个新的吧。 6. The marching turned to trashing. 游行队伍开始动手捣毁东西了。', '过去式: trashed 过去分词: trashed 现在分词: trashing 第三人称单数: trashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clamor', '[\'klæmə]', 'n.喧嚷；大声的要求 v.喧嚷；大声要求', '1. A clamor in the press for pollution control. 在报纸上对污染控制的呼吁 2. A din; a clamor. 喧闹; 吵闹 3. They made a clamor for reform. 他们强烈要求改革。 4. The clamor of traffic gave me a headache. 交通噪音让我头痛。', '名词: clamorer 过去式: clamored 过去分词: clamored 现在分词: clamoring 第三人称单数: clamors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('leather', '[\'leðər]', 'n.皮革；皮制品 adj.皮革制的 vt.用皮鞭抽打；用皮革覆盖', '1. This wallet feels to me like leather. 我觉得这钱包像是皮的。 2. Leather can deteriorate in damp conditions. 皮革受潮可变质。 3. Plastic is sometimes used instead of leather. 塑胶有时可以替代皮革。 4. Our factory\'s leather products show genuine leather in its natural colors. 本厂皮制品，还我真皮本色。 5. I have a pair of leather mittens. 我有一副皮连指手套。 6. I\'d like to leather him black and blue. 我要把他揍得青一块紫一块的。', '过去式: leathered 过去分词: leathered 现在分词: leathering 第三人称单数: leathers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rough', '[rʌf]', 'adj.粗糙的；粗略的，大概的；粗暴的；艰难的；讨厌的；不适的；汹涌的 adv.粗糙地；粗暴地 n.粗制品；暴徒；高低不平的路面 vt.使粗糙；殴打；草拟', '1. The rough road made the car vibrate. 崎岖不平的道路使车颠簸得很厉害。 2. You\'d better give us a rough idea of your price. 您最好给我们一个粗略的价格。 3. It is only a rough guide to ideal weight. 这只是一个实现理想体重的粗略的办法。 4. They complained rough handling by the police. 他们抱怨受到警察粗野的对待。 5. He is now able to play rough and tumble with the other kids. 现在他可以粗暴地摔倒其他孩子了。 6. I think that new singer is a diamond in the rough. 我觉得那个新歌手是块未经雕琢的玉。 7. Micro-exfoliators help slough away rough, dull, uneven skin for a more radiant complexion. 细腻的磨砂颗粒帮助去除被溶解的角质，使粗糙晦暗不均匀的皮肤重现柔嫩和光泽。', '副词: roughly 比较级: rougher 最高级: roughest 名词: rougher 过去式: roughed 过去分词: roughed 现在分词: roughing 第三人称单数: roughs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recollection', '[ˌrekə\'lekʃn]', 'n.回忆；记忆力；记忆；回忆起的事物', '1. I have no recollection at all of my childhood. 我完全记不起我的儿童时代了。 2. They have not been here within my recollection. 我记得他们从未到过这里。 3. His recollection of the campaign is not too clear. 他对竞选的记忆不是那么清楚。 4. That evening together is one of my happiest recollections. 我们一起欢度的那个晚上是我最快乐的事情之一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reverence', '[\'revərəns]', 'n.敬畏；尊敬；尊严 v.尊敬；敬畏；崇敬 Reverence: 对某些基督教神职人员的尊称.', '1. Their assistants also lorded it over the people.But out of reverence for God I did not act like that. 连他们的仆人也辖制人民，但我因为敬畏神，就不这样行。 2. All countries have a native spiritual tradition based around reverence for the forces of nature. 所有国家都有本国基于敬畏自然力量的精神传统。 3. These students have reverence for their teacher. 这些学生很尊敬他们的老师。 4. They always hold our teachers in reverence. 他们一向尊敬老师。 5. These students have reverence for their teacher. 这些学生很尊敬他们的老师。', '名词: reverencer 过去式: reverenced 过去分词: reverenced 现在分词: reverencing 第三人称单数: reverences');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('harry', '[\'hæri]', 'vt.不断骚扰；打扰；侵扰；侵掠 n.哈里（人名）', '1. We have to harry him for money. 我们不得不常常缠着他要钱。 2. The tax authorities have been harrying her for repayment. 税务当局不断逼她缴税。 3. He was harried by constant bothering of his fans. 他的崇拜者的不断打扰令他十分苦恼。 4. The army harried the enemy\'s border. 军队不断地袭扰敌方的边境。', '过去式: harried 过去分词: harried 现在分词: harrying 第三人称单数: harries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('waddle', '[\'wɑːdl]', 'v.蹒跚而行；摇摇摆摆地走 n.摇摆的步子；蹒跚', '1. A short plump woman came waddling along the pavement. 有个矮胖女子一摇一摆地沿人行道走来。 2. It was very funny the way in which the penguins used to waddle . 企鹅走路的那样子真是滑稽。 3. He headed towards her at a breakneck waddle. 他一摇一摆迅速朝她身边跑去。', '名词: waddler 过去式: waddled 过去分词: waddled 现在分词: waddling 第三人称单数: waddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mansion', '[\'mænʃn]', 'n.大厦；宅邸；公寓', '1. The family owns a lordly mansion. 那个家族拥有一座气派的大厦。 2. The portal of the mansion looks magnificent. 这座大厦的正门看上去富丽堂皇。 3. The poor girl was astonished by the sumptuous furnishings of the mansion. 这个贫穷的女孩被大厦里的豪华的陈设惊呆了。 4. The broad steps in front of the mansion made it look very dignified. 宽阔的台阶使大厦的正面显得很气派。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('code', '[koʊd]', 'n.密码；法规；准则 v.制成法典；把 ... 编码', '1. I can break the code of this box. 我能破译这个箱子的密码。 2. She tapped out in code to headquarters. 她给总部发出密码电报。 3. The Highway Code has been carried out. 公路法规已经被执行。 4. Managers are expected to comply with the company\'s code of conduct. 希望经理能够遵守公司的行为准则。 5. They coded each sample and sent them to the lab for analysis. 他们把每个样本都编了代码并送到实验室分析。', '过去式: coded 过去分词: coded 现在分词: coding 第三人称单数: codes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dual', '[\'duːəl]', 'adj.双重的；成双的 n.双数', '1. She has dual nationality. 她有双重国籍。 2. His dual role as a composer and a conductor made him very busy. 他作曲家和指挥家的双重身份使他非常繁忙。 3. The car has dual exhaust pipes. 这车有双排气管。', '副词: dually');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consolidate', '[kən\'sɒləˌdeɪt]', 'v.合并；统一；巩固', '1. The two companies consolidated last year. 这两个公司去年合并了。 2. We will consolidate and deliver together then. 我们届时将提前统一运输。 3. He bribes his leader to consolidate his position. 他贿赂他的领导来巩固他的地位。 4. We\'ve made a good start, now it\'s time to consolidate. 我们有了一个良好的开端, 现在应该加以巩固。', '名词: consolidator 过去式: consolidated 过去分词: consolidated 现在分词: consolidating 第三人称单数: consolidates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ravenous', '[\'rævənəs]', 'adj.贪婪的；极饿的', '1. The country has also become a ravenous consumer. 这个国家还成为一个贪婪的消费者。 2. The ravenous lion tore the quarry. 饥饿的狮子撕碎了猎物。 3. The ravenous children ate everything on the table. 饿极了的孩子把桌上所有东西吃掉了。', '副词: ravenously 名词: ravenousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relative', '[\'relətɪv]', 'adj.相对的；比较的；相关的 n.亲戚；[语]关系词', '1. Motion is absolute while stagnation is relative. 运动是绝对的,而静止是相对的。 2. They are now living in relative comfort. 他们现在过着比较安逸的生活。 3. Relative to the size, the city is sparsely populated. 与其面积相比, 这个城市的人口是稀少的。 4. The teacher asked me some questions relative to my paper. 老师问了我一些和我的论文有关的问题。 5. He showed such concern that people took him to be a relative. 他很关心别人，因而大家都把他当作亲人。', '名词: relativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aluminum', '[ə\'luːmɪnəm]', 'n.铝 =aluminium（英）.', '1. A metallurgical coating process in which iron or steel is immersed in a powder of another metal, such as zinc, chromium, or aluminum, and heated to a temperature below the melting point of either. 渗碳处理一种冶金镀膜工序，在此工序中把钢或铁浸入另一种金属如锌、铬或铝的粉剂里，并加热至这一金属的熔点温度以下 2. She put some noodles in the aluminum saucepan. 她在铝锅里下了些面条。 3. Aluminum is a kind of light silvery metal. 铝是一种轻薄并呈银色的金属。 4. Aluminum foil can be used for wrapping food. 铝箔用于包装食物。', '简写符号: Al');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beguile', '[bɪ\'ɡaɪl]', 'v.诱骗；使陶醉；哄；消磨', '1. The travelers were beguiled by the beauty of the landscapes. 游客们被景色的美丽所陶醉。 2. He beguiled me into lending him my bicycle. 他骗我把自行车借给了他。', '副词: beguilingly 名词: beguilement 过去式: beguiled 过去分词: beguiled 现在分词: beguiling 第三人称单数: beguiles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mineral', '[\'mɪnərəl]', 'n.矿物(石）；矿物质', '1. Coal is a mineral. 煤是一种矿物。 2. We are digging for mineral deposits. 我们正在掘地探矿。 3. This shop sells mineral water. 这家商店卖矿泉水。 4. They have sold up ten crates of mineral water in the afternoon. 他们这个下午卖掉了十箱矿泉水。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inflammation', '[ˌɪnflə\'meɪʃn]', 'n.发炎；炎症；燃烧；激动', '1. He has an inflammation of the lungs. 他得了肺炎。 2. Many babies develop a mild inflammation in the eyes a few days after birth. 许多婴孩出生几天以后眼睛会有轻微的发炎。 3. Inflammation plays a major role in these processes. 炎症在以上过程中起了重要的作用。 4. The submucosa shows intense inflammation. 黏膜下层有严重的炎症。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consecutive', '[kən\'sekjətɪv]', 'adj.连续的；连贯的', '1. It has rained for four consecutive days. 已连续下了四天雨。 2. He was re-elected for four consecutive terms. 他连着四届当选。 3. The policy of our Party is consecutive. 我党的政策始终如一。', '副词: consecutively 名词: consecutiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immigrant', '[\'ɪmɪɡrənt]', 'n.移民；侨民', '1. He admitted that he was an illegal immigrant. 他承认他是非法移民。 2. California has many immigrants from other states. 加利福尼亚有许多来自其他州的移民。 3. Immigrant workers were classed as aliens. 移民来的工人已归入侨民类。 4. His father is of native Indian extraction and his mother an immigrant Italian. 他父亲有印第安土著血统，母亲是意大利侨民。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hypothesis', '[haɪ\'pɑːθəsɪs]', 'n.假说；假设；前提；猜测', '1. The hypothesis promptly attracted some interest. 这个假说很快引起了注意。 2. The validity of the hypothesis can be tested. 这种假说的可靠性是经得起考验的。 3. His hypothesis turned out to be correct. 事实证明他的假设是正确的。 4. The survey result consisted with our hypothesis. 调查结果和我们的假设相一致。', '名词复数: hypotheses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('column', '[\'kɑːləm]', 'n.栏；专栏；列；圆柱；柱；柱形物', '1. And in this column, you write down everything in the parcel. 在这一栏里,您要写上包裹里每一件东西。 2. He used to write a column for this newspaper. 他过去曾为这家报纸写专栏文章。 3. A blank column row is inserted. 此时,将插入一个空白列行。 4. The temple is supported by massive columns. 此庙由粗大的柱子支撑。', '形容词: columned');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('herald', '[\'herəld]', 'n.使者；传令官；先驱；预兆 vt.预报；标志', '1. The robin is a herald of spring. 知更鸟是预告春天到来的使者. 2. The cuckoo is the herald of the spring. 杜鹃报春。 3. He had the important manner of an official herald. 他像个神气十足的官方传令官。 4. He became a reporter for the Herald Tribune. 他成为《先驱论坛报》的记者。 5. To us this oracular remark seemed to herald Hitler. 这番玄妙深奥的话在我们看来仿佛预示着希特勒的来临。', '过去式: heralded 过去分词: heralded 现在分词: heralding 第三人称单数: heralds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inept', '[ɪ\'nept]', 'adj.不适当的；无能的；笨拙的', '1. Only inept officials would burden children with such a requirement rather than install speed bumps, others insisted. 另有人认为，只有无能的官员才会用这样的规定来加重孩子们的负担，而不采取安装减速装置。 2. Why do you give me this tainted Apocrypha, this thousandth copy, this inept falsification? 为什么给我这本污损过的伪经，这第一千次的抄本，笨拙的伪造？', '副词: ineptly 名词: ineptness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assiduous', '[ə\'sɪdʒuəs]', 'adj.勤勉的；刻苦的', '1. He was assiduous in performance of duty. 他勤勉地履行职责。 2. The book was the result of ten years of assiduous research. 那本书是十年苦心钻研的成果。', '副词: assiduously 名词: assiduousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shipment', '[\'ʃɪpmənt]', 'n.装运；货物；装船；出货', '1. Better to postpone the shipment than to cancel the contract. 与其撤约还不如延期装运。 2. We have reached an agreement with him in regard to the shipment. 我们已经就装运问题同他达成协议。 3. A signed invoice presumes receipt of the shipment. 经过签字的发票表示货物已经收到。 4. The merchant had received a shipment of tea. 这个商人收到了一船茶叶。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crisscross', '[\'krɪsˌkrɒs]', 'v.交叉；来回移动 adj.交叉的；十字形的 n.十字形', '1. An open framework made of strips of metal, wood, or similar material overlapped or overlaid in a regular, usually crisscross pattern. 格构开放式格架，由金属片。木片或相类似原料搭叠成格状，通常用交叉方式构成 2. An open, crisscross pattern or weave. 格子细工开放式交叉结构或编织法', '过去式: crisscrossed 过去分词: crisscrossed 现在分词: crisscrossing 第三人称单数: crisscrosses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apprentice', '[ə\'prentɪs]', 'n.学徒；见习生 v.使当学徒', '1. He began his career as an apprentice. 他以当学徒开始他的职业生涯。 2. The shop is taking on two new apprentices. 这个商店新收了两个学徒。 3. He is an apprentice plumber. 他是个见习水管工人。 4. The two pilots and an apprentice pilot were among those killed. 遇难者中包括两名飞行员和一名见习飞行员。 5. The boy was apprenticed to a carpenter. 这个男孩被送去学木匠。', '名词: apprenticeship 过去式: apprenticed 过去分词: apprenticed 现在分词: apprenticing 第三人称单数: apprentices');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('celebrity', '[sə\'lebrəti]', 'n.名人；名誉；社会名流', '1. She became a celebrity overnight. 她一下变成名人了。 2. He was voted the worst dressed celebrity. 大家一致认为他是衣着最差的名人。 3. Celebrity, money and possessions are too often the touchstones for teenagers. 名誉、金钱和财产常常成为青少年们衡量事物的标准。 4. She achieved celebrity status overnight. 她一夜之间成为名流。', '名词: celebrityhood 名词复数: celebrities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('celebrated', '[\'selɪbreɪtɪd]', 'adj.著名的；声誉卓著的 动词celebrate的过去式和过去分词.', '1. The celebrated violinist was mobbed by the audience. 观众团团围住了这位著名的小提琴演奏家。 2. This is celebrated as the Onam festival in Kerala, where he is also called Maveli. 这在印度西南部喀拉拉邦著名的奥南节也有庆祝，他也被称为玛瓦利。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boredom', '[\'bɔːrdəm]', 'n.无聊；厌烦；厌倦；令人厌烦的事物', '1. Unemployment can drive you mad with boredom. 失业会让你无聊得发疯。 2. The best cure for boredom is hard work. 治疗无聊最好的办法是努力工作。 3. He found the boredom scarcely endurable. 他觉得这种厌烦难以忍受。 4. Boredom is not a ground for divorce. 日久生厌不能成为离婚的理由。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('surmise', '[sər\'maɪz]', 'n.推测 vt.推测；臆测', '1. It turned out that my surmise was correct. 结果表明我的推测没有错。 2. I surmise that he will take the job. 我推测他会接受这份工作。 3. They surmise that inflation in services is being underestimated, causing real growth to be overstated. 他们推测是因为低估了服务领域的通胀，因此实际增长才会被高估。', '过去式: surmised 过去分词: surmised 现在分词: surmising 第三人称单数: surmises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pitiful', '[\'pɪtɪfl]', 'adj.慈悲的；可怜的；凄惨的', '1. The patient was in a pitiful condition. 那个病人处于一种非常可怜的状况。 2. What a pitiful man he is! You should help him. 多可怜的人啊 3. The ruined house after the earthquake looked a pitiful sight. 地震后倒塌的房屋一片凄惨景象。 4. I never saw a sight so pitiful as this before! 我从来没有见过这样惨的事情！', '副词: pitifully 名词: pitifulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intuitive', '[ɪn\'tuːɪtɪv]', 'adj.直觉的', '1. Are women more intuitive than men? 女子比男子的直觉力更强吗? 2. She is outgoing, naturally cheerful, and intuitive. 她外向、生愉悦以及具备敏锐的直觉。 3. Her perception of the right seemed almost intuitive. 她对正确事物的理解几乎是直觉的。 4. This is an art in which intuitive guessing plays an important part. 这个工作需要技巧，直觉的猜测会起很大的作用', '副词: intuitively 名词: intuitiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quote', '[kwoʊt]', 'v.引述；报价；举证 n.引用', '1. She asked the reporter not to quote her remarks. 她要求记者不要引述她的话。 2. Please quote your price in terms of pound. 请您报盘时用英镑报价。 3. Can you quote me a recent instance? 你能给我举一个最近的例子吗？ 4. A direct quote was taken from his speech. 直接引用他的演讲。', '名词: quoter 过去式: quoted 过去分词: quoted 现在分词: quoting 第三人称单数: quotes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('noxious', '[\'nɑːkʃəs]', 'adj.<正式>有害的；有毒的', '1. Noxious gases had built up in the sewer. 下水道 的有害气体越积越多。 2. Noxious chemicals are found in the river water. 河水里发现了有毒化学物品。 3. We must trace the source of these noxious gases. 我们必须查出毒气的来源。', '副词: noxiously 名词: noxiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('titanic', '[taɪ\'tænɪk]', 'adj.巨大的；[化]钛的 n.[T-]泰坦尼克号（船名）', '1. Four days after the Titanic set out, a very big iceberg floated towards her. 泰坦尼克号出发四天以后，一座巨大的冰山向它漂来。 2. The Titanic and all her crew were in Davy Jones\'s locker. 泰坦尼克号及其全体船员均都葬身鱼腹。 3. He owns a detailed miniature of the Titanic. 他有一艘泰坦尼克号的精致小模型。', '副词: titanically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('currency', '[\'kɜːrənsi]', 'n.货币；流通', '1. The president proclaimed that a new currency would be issued. 总统宣布将发行新货币。 2. Our currency will not be depreciated. 我们的货币不会贬值。 3. There are currency restrictions on the sums allowed for foreign travel. 到国外旅行允许携带的款额有所限制。 4. The word has attained general currency. 这个词已经通用起来了。', '名词复数: currencies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boundary', '[\'baʊndri]', 'n.边界；分界线', '1. We crossed the state boundary at midnight. 我们在午夜穿过了州界。 2. They marked the boundaries of the football fields. 他们画出了足球场地的边界。 3. Scientists continue to push back the boundaries of knowledge. 科学家不断地把知识领域的边缘向外扩展。 4. The lane is the boundary of our land from theirs. 那条小路就是我们这片地与他们那片地的分界线。', '名词复数: boundaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lower', '[\'loʊər]', 'adj.低的；下级的；下层的 v.降低；减弱；跌落', '1. The publisher paid his hacks low. 出版商付给他雇佣的文人很低的费用。 2. He because of bashful but low head. 他因羞愧而低下了头。 3. The lower level is subordinate to the higher level. 下级服从上级。 4. He belongs to the lower middle class. 他来自中产阶级下层。 5. Don\'t lower yourself by asking him for help. 不要向他求助以免降低身分。', '副词: loweringly 异体字: lour 过去式: lowered/loured 过去分词: lowered/loured 现在分词: lowering/louring 第三人称单数: lowers/lours');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adaptable', '[ə\'dæptəbl]', 'adj.能适应的；适应性强的；可改编的', '1. Any coupling device must be adaptable to obtain reasonable performance in all expected situations. 所有联结设备在所有期望的情况一定是能适应的得到合理的表现。 2. The adaptable Indian rhino is intermediate in size. 适应性强的印度犀牛是中等体型的。 3. This multi-skilling approach will provide the organization with an adaptable workforce. 多功能技术的办法，给组织提供了一个适应性强的劳动力。', '名词: adaptability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lithe', '[laɪð]', 'adj.柔软的；易弯的；轻盈的', '1. Little babies have lithe bodies. 小孩有柔软的身体。 2. A lithe willow is waggling back and forth by the wind. 易弯曲的柳树因为风的吹拂而不停摇摆。 3. Her movements in free gymnastics are lithe and graceful. 她的自由体操动作轻盈优美。', '副词: lithely 比较级: lither 最高级: lithest 名词: litheness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clinch', '[klɪntʃ]', 'v.钉牢；紧抓；扭住对手；最终解决 n.揪扭；拥抱；固定', '1. We realize that it is not easy to clinch the medals. 大家意识到想夺取奖牌已经不是那么容易了。 2. Mike Bryan talked about getting the chance to clinch the victory. 麦克布莱恩表达了拥抱胜利的喜悦。 3. The boxers clinch and the referee have to separate them. 拳击手扭抱在一起，裁判让他们分开。 4. We clinched the agreement with a handshake. 我们握手达成协议。 5. When the police came the fighters were in a clinch. 警察到来时，打架的人正扭成一团。', '过去式: clinched 过去分词: clinched 现在分词: clinching 第三人称单数: clinches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('probe', '[proʊb]', 'n.调查；查究；探针；探测器 v.用探针测；探测；详细调查', '1. They launched a probe into the disappearance of government funds. 他们发起了对政府资金流失一事的调查. 2. Pressure on the industry was building even before the latest probe. 事实上,在最近的调查之前,压力就已经在这个行业聚集。 3. The image sent back by the probe is very clear. 探针传回的图像非常清晰。 4. The brain surgeon asked the nurse to pass him a probe. 脑外科医生要护士将探针递给他。 5. The doctor will probe your stomach with a camera. 医生会用带摄像头的胃镜检查你的胃。', '副词: probingly 名词: prober 过去式: probed 过去分词: probed 现在分词: probing 第三人称单数: probes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delete', '[dɪ\'liːt]', 'vt.删除', '1. Delete his name from the list. 把他的名字从名单上删去。 2. The attack is to wipe out data, to delete flies, or to format the hard disk. 常见的攻击方式是消除数据、删除文件或者格式化硬盘。 3. Please delete my name from your list. 请把我的名字从你的名单上删除。 4. You cannot delete your standard resource. 您不能删除您的标准资源。', '过去式: deleted 过去分词: deleted 现在分词: deleting 第三人称单数: deletes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('desire', '[dɪ\'zaɪər]', 'n.渴望；愿望；欲望 v.渴望；向往；要求', '1. I am filled with the desire to go back home. 我心中充满了回家的渴望。 2. Young people have no desire to work for the government. 年轻人没有在政府部门工作的意愿。 3. Her desire to dominate other people has caused trouble in her family. 她想支配他人的欲望在家庭中引起了麻烦。 4. She desires for a breakthrough in her research. 她渴望自己的研究能够出现突破。', '名词: desirer 过去式: desired 过去分词: desired 现在分词: desiring 第三人称单数: desires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tacit', '[\'tæsɪt]', 'adj.心照不宣的；缄默的；默示的', '1. They have a tacit understanding. 他俩心照不宣。 2. Our tacit treaty with her was that we could play on her lawn. 我们和她心照不宣的协定是，我们可以在她的草坪上玩。 3. The deal had the tacit approval of the President. 这笔交易得到总统的默许。 4. They were leagued together by a tacit treaty. 他们根据默契关系联合起来了。', '副词: tacitly 名词: tacitness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vacant', '[\'veɪkənt]', 'adj.空虚的；空的；木然的', '1. Absence of occupation is not rest, a mind quite vacant is a mind distress. 无所事事不是休息，十分空虚的心灵是痛苦的心灵。 2. The sky remains infinitely vacant for earth there to build its heaven with dreams. 天空总是无限空虚地用梦在大地构筑天堂。 3. He was appointed to the vacant post. 他被委派填补那空缺。 4. There are some vacant offices on the third floor. 四楼有几间空著的办公室。', '副词: vacantly 名词: vacantness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('religion', '[rɪ\'lɪdʒən]', 'n.宗教；宗教信仰', '1. He is a disciple of religion. 他是宗教信徒。 2. Jesus was the founder of the Christian religion. 耶稣是基督教的创始人。 3. Politics and religion are daily topics of conversation. 政治和宗教是人们平常交谈的主要话题。 4. There are many religions in the world. 世界上有许多种宗教信仰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aroma', '[ə\'roʊmə]', 'n.浓香；香气', '1. The aroma of coffee always cheers me up. 咖啡的浓香总能给我一份好心情。 2. Their attributes are a golden colour, a fruity aroma and a smooth flavour. 他们的归属是一个金制的颜色，水果的浓香和一个平滑的滋味。 3. Its delicate aroma is sweet and appealing. 其微妙的香气是甜的吸引力。 4. The green coffee beans have no flavor or aroma. 生咖啡豆既没有味道也没有香气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('counterfeit', '[\'kaʊntərfɪt]', 'n.膺品；伪造品 adj.假冒的；假装的 v.仿造；伪装；假装', '1. This ten-dollar bill is a counterfeit. 这张十元钞票是伪钞。 2. We suspect the paper to be a counterfeit. 我们疑心这个证件是伪造的。 3. This note is counterfeit, but that one\'s good. 这张钞票是假的，那张是真的。 4. And eyes will be very difficult to counterfeit. 而且眼睛将是非常难以仿造的。', '名词: counterfeiter 过去式: counterfeited 过去分词: counterfeited 现在分词: counterfeiting 第三人称单数: counterfeits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('castigate', '[\'kæstɪɡeɪt]', 'v.惩罚；严厉批评；谴责', '1. Reconnoitring and collecting evidence is the first step to castigate such crime. 侦查与取证是打击这种犯罪的第一步。 2. She could not find sufficient reproaches with which to castigate herself. 她找不出充分的理由非难自己。', '名词: castigation 过去式: castigated 过去分词: castigated 现在分词: castigating 第三人称单数: castigates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('documentary', '[ˌdɑːkju\'mentri]', 'n.纪录片 adj.纪实的；文件形式的', '1. The film was a documentary on politicians in Russia. 这部电影是一部关于俄罗斯政坛的纪录片。 2. We were watching a documentary about Canadian sports. 我们在观看关于加拿大体育的纪录片。 3. Her latest documentary is concerned with youth unemployment. 她最近的一部纪录片是关于青年人失业问题的。 4. The film was given a documentary style by the director. 导演以纪实的表现手法拍摄了这部影片。', '名词复数: documentaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unify', '[\'juːnɪfaɪ]', 'vt.使统一、使成为一体', '1. The new leader hopes to unify the country. 新领袖希望把国家统一起来。 2. England and Scotland do not have a unified legal system. 英格兰和苏格兰法制不统一.', '形容词: unifiable 名词: unification 过去式: unified 过去分词: unified 现在分词: unifying 第三人称单数: unifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ally', '[\'ælaɪ]', 'n.同盟国；同盟者；伙伴 v.（使）结盟；（使）联合', '1. The ally of the working class was the peasantry. 工人阶级的同盟军是农民阶级。 2. Britain was an ally of America in the World War I. 英国在第一次世界大战中是美国的同盟国。 3. That football team is our ally. 那个足球队是我们的同盟者。 4. Japan is a leading trading partner and security ally of the United States. 日本是美国的主要贸易伙伴和安全盟国。 5. We will ally our forces with the army from the north. 我们将与北方的部队结盟。', '名词复数: allies 过去式: allied 过去分词: allied 现在分词: allying 第三人称单数: allies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('effuse', '[e\'fjuːz]', 'v.流出；散布 adj.散出的；扩散的', '1. The town effuse warmth and hospitality. 这市镇洋溢着人情味和好客精神。 2. Juncus effuse and Bacopa monnieri mixing planted were 26.0% and 23.4%, respectively. 灯心草与过长沙混种吸收率为26.;0%25与23 3. Multiple functions of ultimate room、elegance of luxury two-room，effuse the care of human nature. 功能完善的极品一房、优雅尊贵的奢华两房，极尽人性关怀； 4. This is a robust species with a large, effuse panicle and short-glumed spikelets. 这在粗壮种具大，平展圆锥花序和短小穗。', '过去式: effused 过去分词: effused 现在分词: effusing 第三人称单数: effuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pale', '[peɪl]', 'adj.苍白的；灰白的；暗淡的；无力的 vi.变苍白；变黯淡；相形见绌 n.栅栏', '1. She was pale with fear. 她吓得脸色发白。 2. His pale face has shown his bad health. 他面色苍白，说明他身体不好。 3. The pale eyes seemed to glare past her, the eyebrows frowned, the long jaw hardened. 那双灰白的眼睛仿佛看穿了她的身子，眉头皱着，长下巴发僵。 4. This pale child of the Parisian faubourgs livesdevelops, makes connections, \"grows supple\" in suffering, in the presence of social realitiesof human things, a thoughtful witness. 巴黎近郊的脸色灰白的孩子，面对着令人深省的社会现实和人间事物，活着，成长着，在苦难中沉下去，浮上来。 5. She paled with shock at the news. 她听到那消息大惊失色。', '副词: palely 比较级: paler 最高级: palest 名词: paleness 过去式: paled 过去分词: paled 现在分词: paling 第三人称单数: pales');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('precise', '[prɪ\'saɪs]', 'adj.精确的；恰好的；准确的；严格的', '1. With the new technique, measurement was claimed to be much more precise. 有了这种技术,人们断言测量的结果会精确得多。 2. At the precise moment that I put my foot on the step, the bus started. 恰恰就在我登上公共汽车踏板的时候，车子开动了。 3. I am not clear about the precise bearing of the word in this passage. 我说不准这个字在这段文章里的确切意义是什么。 4. Precise employees are highly appreciated in our company. 我们公司十分欣赏工作态度严谨的员工。', '名词: preciseness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extent', '[ɪk\'stent]', 'n. 广度； 宽度； 长度； 大小； 范围； 程度 n. [律]<英>扣押； <美>临时所有权令', '1. A particle has no extent so that its position is a point. 质点没有广度因此它的位置是一个点。 2. As a result, the Census Bureau should obtain a better picture of the extent of intermarriage in the United States. 这样，人口普查局就能够更好地了解美国异族通婚的广度。 3. Percentage increase in extent size. 范围大小增加的百分比。 4. The extent of the regions was determined by the descriptor basicity. 这三个数据区的范围大小是由算符的碱性度决定的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('launch', '[lɔːntʃ]', 'v.发起；推出（新产品）；发射；使(船)下水 n.发射；产品推介', '1. We were going to launch a counterattack. 我们准备发起反攻。 2. The company researched the market demand and decided to launch their new product. 这家公司调查了市场需求，决定推出新产品。 3. The people all over the country exulted in the success in launching a new satellite. 全国人民为成功地发射了一颗新的人造卫星而欢欣鼓舞。 4. The oil tanker was launched last year. 那艘油轮去年下水了。 5. The launch was delayed by a technical hitch . 由于技术上出现临时故障而发射延期.', '过去式: launched 过去分词: launched 现在分词: launching 第三人称单数: launches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('navigation', '[ˌnævɪ\'ɡeɪʃn]', 'n.导航；航行；航海', '1. Mechanics discovered problems with the plane\'s navigation system. 机械工发现飞机的导航系统存在问题。 2. Navigation is difficult on this river because of the hide rock. 因为有暗礁，在这条河上航行很困难。 3. The compass is an instrument of navigation. 罗盘是航行仪器。 4. The canal has been opened up to steam navigation. 运河已经可以航行轮船。', '形容词: navigational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('satisfactory', '[ˌsætɪs\'fæktəri]', 'adj.令人满意的', '1. The efficacy of the medicine is satisfactory. 这药的药效令人满意。 2. His general state of health is fairly satisfactory. 他总的健康状况相当令人满意。 3. You must accept the result, satisfactory or otherwise. 你必须接受这个结果，满意也好不满意也好。 4. Everything was turning out most satisfactory. 一切都非常趁心如意。', '副词: satisfactorily 名词: satisfactoriness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spill', '[spɪl]', 'v.溢出；洒；使 ... 流出；泄漏 n.溢出；流；木片；小杆', '1. The coffee is so full that it might spill over. 咖啡太满可能会溢出来。 2. Put the cap back on the bottle, otherwise the juice will spill. 把瓶盖儿盖好，要不汁液就洒出来了。 3. Take care not to spill a drop of the medicine. 注意一滴药也不要洒。 4. The sway of the pail cause some milk to spill out. 桶的摇晃使一些牛奶溢了出来。 5. The oil spill endangered thousands of birds. 石油的溢泄危及成千上万的鸟儿。', '名词: spiller 过去式: spilled/spilt 过去分词: spilled/spilt 现在分词: spilling 第三人称单数: spills');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avaricious', '[ˌævə\'rɪʃəs]', 'adj.贪财的；贪婪的', '1. He is so avaricious that we call him a blood sucker. 他如此贪婪, 我们都叫他吸血鬼。 2. Midas is a legendary king of Phrygia who was insatiably avaricious. 迈达斯是传说中弗律癸亚国的国王，他是一个贪得无厌的人。', '副词: avariciously 名词: avariciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stagecoach', '[\'steɪdʒkoʊtʃ]', 'n.驿马车；公共马车', '1. The stagecoach driver cracked the whip. 驿站马车的车夫抽响了鞭子。 2. The stagecoach finally arrived at Gameland at sunrise. 日出时这辆公共马车终于抵达游戏王国。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apprehend', '[ˌæprɪ\'hend]', 'v.理解；忧虑；逮捕；拘押', '1. I can\'t apprehend your meaning. 我不明白你的意思。 2. He can\'t apprehend the real nature of change. 他不能理解变革的真实性质。 3. Do you apprehend there will be any difficulty? 你怕有任何困难吗？ 4. This will help them to apprehend the rapist. 这将有助于警察逮捕强奸犯。', '过去式: apprehended 过去分词: apprehended 现在分词: apprehending 第三人称单数: apprehends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sophisticated', '[sə\'fɪstɪkeɪtɪd]', 'adj.老练的；精密的；复杂的；久经世故的', '1. She is such a sophisticated woman that she saw through his trick at the first sight. 她是个十分老练的女人,她一眼就看穿了他的把戏。 2. As far as defense is concerned, we need to buy more sophisticated weapons. 就防御的观点来说，我们需要购买更多精密的武器。 3. The publisher\'s techniques for the promotion of his books have become increasingly sophisticated since the 1950s. 自20世纪50年代以来,出版商推销书籍的方式愈加复杂。 4. I\'d rather deal with a simple man than a sophisticated man. 我宁愿与纯朴的人打交道,不愿与世故的人交往。', '副词: sophisticatedly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rumble', '[\'rʌmbl]', 'n. 隆隆声； 辘辘声 n. (旧式汽车车厢后的)折叠加座 <俚>打群架 v. 发隆隆声； 使辘辘响', '1. We heard the occasional rumble of a passing truck. 我们偶尔听到卡车驶过的隆隆声。 2. Far below I could hear the rumble of tube trains carrying commuters to the West End. 我能听到把使用月票的乘客送往西区的地铁火车在地下深处行驶时发出的隆隆声。 3. We heard the occasional rumble of a passing truck. 我们偶尔听到卡车驶过的隆隆声。 4. Far below I could hear the rumble of tube trains carrying commuters to the West End. 我能听到把使用月票的乘客送往西区的地铁火车在地下深处行驶时发出的隆隆声。', '形容词: rumbly 副词: rumblingly 名词: rumbler 过去式: rumbled 过去分词: rumbled 现在分词: rumbling 第三人称单数: rumbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mythology', '[mɪ\'θɑːlədʒi]', 'n.神话；神话学；神话集', '1. He studies Greek and Roman mythology. 他研究希腊和罗马神话。 2. It is a mythology about the king. 这是个关于国王的神话。 3. Modern mythology in China appeared as an interaction between western theory of myth and native tradition of Chinese learning. 中国现代神话学是在引进西方学理与继承本土学统的过程中建立起来的。', '名词复数: mythologies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('situated', '[\'sɪtʃueɪtɪd]', 'adj.位于；处于 ...境地的 动词situate的过去式和过去分词', '1. The school is situated just outside the town. 学校就位于镇子的外面。 2. Most of China is situated in the temperate zone. 中国大部分地区处于温带。 3. The corporation is rather awkwardly situated. 公司处境相当尴尬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inertia', '[ɪ\'nɜːrʃə]', 'n.惯性；惰性', '1. Inertia carried the car to the pavement. 惯性使汽车驶到了人行道上。 2. Inertia is evident in our every day experiences. 惯性在我们日常生活中是很常见的。 3. Everyone has his psychological inertia, or in some way, indolence. 每个人都有一种思维惯性或者说惰性。 4. Because of the sheer inertia of the system many badly needed reform is never introduced. 纯粹是由於制度本身有惰性，很多事急需改革却从未实行。', '形容词: inertial 副词: inertially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('befuddle', '[bɪ\'fʌdəl]', 'vt.使昏迷；使迷惑；使烂醉', '1. The new arrival was befuddled by the rapid-fire conversation. 新到达者被连珠炮似的谈话弄糊涂了。 2. Don\'t befuddle me with all those masses of detail. 不要拿一大堆琐事把我搞迷糊。 3. He also fabricates sensational lies to befuddle world opinion. 他也编造耸人听闻的谎言欺骗世界舆论。 4. John is very amusing when he is completely befuddled. 当约翰喝得完全糊涂了的时候，他非常有趣儿。', '过去式: befuddled 过去分词: befuddled 现在分词: befuddling 第三人称单数: befuddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enrich', '[ɪn\'rɪtʃ]', 'vt.使富足；使肥沃；使丰富', '1. The expanding economy enriched the peasants. 不断发展的经济使农民们富裕起来。 2. The library was enriched with new books. 购买新书使图书馆得到了充实。 3. Farmers enrich the soil with organic and inorganic manures. 农民用有机肥料和无机肥料来提高土壤的肥力。 4. An appreciation of art will enrich your life. 艺术欣赏将会丰富你的生活', '名词: enricher 过去式: enriched 过去分词: enriched 现在分词: enriching 第三人称单数: enriches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('minority', '[maɪ\'nɔːrəti]', 'n.少数；少数民族；未成年', '1. Only a minority of British households do not have a car. 英国只有少数家庭没有汽车。 2. A small minority voted against the motion. 投票反对该提议的人占少数。 3. The question of which state the minority group should belong to was decided by (a) plebiscite. 该少数民族应归属哪一州的问题已由公民投票表决。 4. There are 56 minorities in our country. 我国有56个少数民族。', '名词复数: minorities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('neon', '[\'niːɑːn]', 'n.氖；霓虹灯', '1. Helium and neon are inert gases. 氦和氖为惰性气体。 2. Thompson was able to demonstrate the existence of two isotopes of neon. 汤普森能证明氖有两种同位素存在。 3. A neon sign must be electrified. 霓虹灯必须通电。 4. The neon light has lit up the area. 霓虹灯照亮了那带区域。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hue', '[hjuː]', 'n.色调；色彩；样子；意味；信仰；喊叫', '1. The cool hue in the picture is distinct from the other ones. 这幅画的冷色调与其他画截然不同。 2. Her normally rosy face took on a deeper hue. 她平常玫瑰色的脸上呈现出更深的色彩。 3. The diamond shone with every hue under the sun. 这颗钻石在阳光下显得色彩斑斓。 4. This puts a different hue on the matter. 这么一来,事情的性质就不一样了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('miracle', '[\'mɪrəkl]', 'n.奇迹', '1. Her life was saved by a miracle. 她的生命是靠奇迹救活的。 2. The compact disc is a miracle of modern technology. 激光唱片是当代技术的奇葩。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fertilize', '[\'fɜːrtəlaɪz]', 'v.施肥；使肥沃；使丰富；[生]使受精；使受粉', '1. I help my father fertilize the crops. 我帮助父亲给农作物施肥。 2. And farmers can use camel west waste to fertilize their crops. 农民能用骆驼的粪便来给农作物施肥。 3. Fertilizer is a substance put on land to fertilize it. 肥料是施在地里使之肥沃的物质。 4. Reading will fertilize his vocabulary. 阅读会丰富他的词汇。', '形容词: fertilizable 过去式: fertilized 过去分词: fertilized 现在分词: fertilizing 第三人称单数: fertilizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('onset', '[\'ɑːnset]', 'n.攻击；进攻；开始', '1. The fierce onset of the enemy broke the ranks of the army. 敌人的猛烈攻击致使全军大乱。 2. Our troops withstood the onset of the enemy. 我们的部队抵挡住了敌人的进攻。 3. The onset of the enemy took us by surprise. 敌人的进攻出乎我们意外。 4. He went to see a doctor at the onset of a fever. 他开始发烧时便去看医生了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confine', '[kən\'faɪn]', 'vt.限制；禁闭 n.范围；界限；约束；限制', '1. I wish the speaker would confine himself to the subject. 我希望演说者不要离题。 2. I am sick, I have to confine to bed. 我病了，我得卧床休息。 3. The thief was confined in a prison. 窃贼被关押在监狱里。 4. Is it cruel to confine a bird in a cage? 把鸟关在笼子里残忍不残忍? 5. This is outside the confines of human knowledge. 这超出了人类知识范畴。', '形容词: confinable 名词: confiner 过去式: confined 过去分词: confined 现在分词: confining 第三人称单数: confines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extension', '[ɪk\'stenʃn]', 'n.延长；伸展；延期；扩充；观念发展；增强 n.电话分机；特别课程 n.[计]文件名', '1. This cord is not long enough! do you have an extension? 这条绳子不够长！你有长一点的吗？ 2. His leg was now capable of full extension. 他的腿现在能够伸展自如了。 3. He asked for an extension of his visa. 他申请延长签证有效期。 4. We built an extension to our house. 我们扩建了我家的房屋。 5. There are telephone extensions in every office. 每间办公室都有电话分机。 6. Method will only return one unique file name per file name extension. 方法对每个文件名扩展名只返回一个唯一文件名。', '形容词: extensional');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prevalent', '[\'prevələnt]', 'adj.流行的；普遍的', '1. Is malaria still prevalent among the populationhere? 疟疾是否仍为此地居民的多发病? 2. Eye diseases are prevalent in some tropical countries. 在一些热带国家，眼疾很流行。 3. This argument was prevalent at the time. 这是当时流行的论调。 4. The prevalent opinion is in favour of reform. 一般舆论都支持改革。', '副词: prevalently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('menu', '[\'menjuː]', 'n.菜单', '1. We only have an a la carte menu. 我们只有分类菜单。 2. He called the waiter to bring the menu. 他叫侍者拿菜单来。 3. I haven\'t decided on the menu yet, let alone bought the food. 我还没决定吃什么菜呢，更不必说买好了。 4. Is fish on the menu today? 今天的菜单上有鱼吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('condense', '[kən\'dens]', 'v.浓缩；凝结；缩短', '1. He condense his speech to half its original length. 他把演讲的长度浓缩了一半。 2. You can condense milk by boiling away much of the water in it. 煮去牛奶中大部分的水分可使它浓缩。 3. Steam condenses into water when cooling down. 蒸汽冷却时凝结成水。 4. Water vapors can condense to form clouds. 水蒸汽能凝结成云。', '形容词: condensable 名词: condensability 过去式: condensed 过去分词: condensed 现在分词: condensing 第三人称单数: condenses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('roam', '[roʊm]', 'v.漫游；闲逛；徜徉', '1. They loved to roam the hills of west Virginia. 他们喜欢在西弗吉尼亚山脉间漫游。 2. Now they roam the Earth, following an insatiable wanderlust. 现在他们漫游地球,跟随一个永不知足的旅行热潮。 3. Bison used to roam through the American great plains, but most of them are slaughter by hunter. 从前野牛在美国大平原上漫游，但是大多数都被猎人屠杀了。 4. The sheep are allowed to roam freely on this land. 绵羊可以在这片地上自由走动。', '名词: roamer 过去式: roamed 过去分词: roamed 现在分词: roaming 第三人称单数: roams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('summon', '[\'sʌmən]', 'vt.召唤；召集；振奋', '1. I\'ve heard the residents of the Infernos will summon a Diety of Fire to honor any hero who brings them the Grail. 我听说地狱的居民会召唤烈火守护神来纪念为他们带来圣杯的英雄。 2. \"A man brags that he can summon the dead. 一个人炫耀说可以召唤死者灵魂。 3. The shareholders were summoned to a general meeting. 那些股东被召集去叁加股东大会。 4. They had to summon a second conference and change the previous decision. 他们不得不召集第二次会议，改变以前的决定。', '名词: summoner 过去式: summoned 过去分词: summoned 现在分词: summoning 第三人称单数: summons');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deserve', '[dɪ\'zɜːrv]', 'vt.应受；值得', '1. He has done nothing to deserve death. 他没做过该受死刑的事。 2. You deserve a reward for being so helpful. 你帮了这么大的忙，理应受到奖励。 3. These proposals deserve careful study. 这些建议值得认真研究。', '过去式: deserved 过去分词: deserved 现在分词: deserving 第三人称单数: deserves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('liaison', '[li\'eɪzɑːn]', 'n.联络；(男女间)私通', '1. Please send us a technical liaison letter about it. 请给我们一份有关此事的技术联络单。 2. He provided a liaison with the guerrillas. 他为游击队提供了联络渠道。 3. He had already contracted a liaison with some girl. 他和某个姑娘私通。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chafe', '[tʃeɪf]', 'v.擦痛；激怒；摩擦 n.擦伤；气恼', '1. A stiff collar may chafe your neck. 硬的衣领会擦伤你的脖子。 2. Her shoes chafed the skin on her feet. 鞋子擦破了她脚上的皮肤。 3. The loud noise chafed him. 吵闹声使他烦躁。 4. Why didn\'t he chafe and become restless? 为什么他没有气急败坏，坐立不安呢?', '过去式: chafed 过去分词: chafed 现在分词: chafing 第三人称单数: chafes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('splendor', '[\'splendə]', 'n.光辉；壮丽；显赫；辉煌', '1. There below lay Paris in all its splendor. 那下面就是光彩夺目的巴黎。 2. Never in his life had he gazed on such splendor. 他生平从没有见过如此壮丽的场面。 3. We admired the splendor of the mountain scenery. 我们赞赏着壮丽的山景。 4. Then the doors of the hall flew open, and showed the whole splendor of a court. 大厅的门一打开,显赫壮观的宫廷景象展现出来了。', '形容词: splendorous');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remit', '[\'riːmɪt]', 'vt.汇出；提交；宽恕；免除；延迟 vi.汇款；缓和；减轻 n.移交事项', '1. He remitted some money to his mother. 他给他母亲寄了一些钱。 2. Remit the interest to her new address. 将利息寄到她的新地址 3. You will have to remit this problem to a higher authority. 你得把这个问题提交给上一级。 4. God would not remit your sins. 上帝不会宽恕你的罪恶。 5. Enclosed is our bill; please remit. 随函寄上账单,请寄款。', '形容词: remittable 名词: remitment 过去式: remitted 过去分词: remitted 现在分词: remitting 第三人称单数: remits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('serene', '[sə\'riːn]', 'adj.安详的；宁静的；平静的 Serene. adj.尊贵的', '1. His serene smile calmed all of us down. 他脸上安详的微笑使我们都冷静下来。 2. The story took place in a serene summer night. 故事发生在一个宁静的夏夜。 3. It was a beautiful morning, calm and serene. 那是一个宁静、明媚的早晨。 4. Light music fills my heart with serene joyfulness. 轻音乐能带给我平静的欢乐。', '副词: serenely 名词: sereneness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proposal', '[prə\'poʊzl]', 'n.求婚；建议；提议', '1. She had had many proposals but preferred to remain single. 许多人向她求过婚, 但她愿过独身生活。 2. The manager made a proposal for uniting the two companies. 经理提出了将两家公司联合起来的建议。 3. Various proposals were put forward by the employees for increasing sales. 员工们摆出了各种提高销售额的提议。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('starch', '[stɑːrtʃ]', 'n.淀粉 vt.给 ... 上浆', '1. Sugar and starch are broken down in the stomach. 糖和淀粉在胃里被分解。 2. You eat too much starch. 你吃的含淀粉的食物太多了。 3. I think there\'s too much starch in their diet. 我看是他们的饮食里淀粉太多了。 4. Starch my shirt\'s collar, please. 请把我的衬衣领浆硬。', '过去式: starched 过去分词: starched 现在分词: starching 第三人称单数: starches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('outing', '[\'aʊtɪŋ]', 'n.郊游；远足；外出', '1. I think we should postpone the outing. 我认为我们应该推迟这次郊游。 2. It is such a fine day for an outing. 今天是这样一个适合于郊游的好日子。 3. We went for an outing on a crisp fall day. 我们在一个秋高气爽的日子去远足了。 4. Our plan for an outing is contingent on the weather. 我们外出游玩的计划视天气而定。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refurbish', '[ˌriː\'fɜːrbɪʃ]', 'vt.刷新；擦亮；再磨光', '1. The flat will be refurbished for the new tenants. 这套房间将重新粉刷以接纳新房客。 2. Our house will be refurbished in the near future. 我们的房子最近将进行翻修。 3. She refurbished all the pots and pans. 她将所有的锅碗瓢盆都擦拭一新。', '名词: refurbishment 过去式: refurbished 过去分词: refurbished 现在分词: refurbishing 第三人称单数: refurbishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stake', '[steɪk]', 'n.桩；赌注；利害关系 v.用桩支撑；下注', '1. He drove a stake into the ground. 他向地里打了一根桩子。 2. This decision puts our lives at stake. 这么一决定,我们的生命就吉凶难卜了。 3. Most parents feel that they have a stake in their children\'s future,and so will use every effort to help them. 大多数家长认为，孩子们的前途和他们有利害关系，所以尽一切努力帮助他们。 4. He put up a stake to support the newly planted tree. 他竖了一根桩支撑新种的树。', '过去式: staked 过去分词: staked 现在分词: staking 第三人称单数: stakes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squeeze', '[skwiːz]', 'v.挤压；塞进；压榨；设法腾出 n.挤压；少量；拥挤；严控；财政困难', '1. Kara squeezed the bottle, and the water rushed out. 卡拉挤压着那个瓶子,水一下子喷了出来。 2. It took some ingenuity to squeeze all the furniture into the little room. 把全部家具都塞进那个小房间是很费了一番心思的。 3. Supermarkets are accused of squeezing both customers and suppliers. 超市因压榨顾客和供货商而遭到指控。 4. I can squeeze a meeting in early tomorrow morning. 我可以在明天清早挤出时间开个会。 5. He gave my hand a gentle squeeze. 他握着我的手,轻轻捏了捏。', '形容词: squeezable 名词: squeezer 过去式: squeezed 过去分词: squeezed 现在分词: squeezing 第三人称单数: squeezes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('formal', '[\'fɔːrml]', 'adj.正式的；正规的；形式的；公开的；拘谨的；有条理的', '1. At the formal party I felt very awkward and out of place. 在正式的舞会上，我感到局促不安，很不自在。 2. This job doesn\'t require any formal training. 这种工作不需要任何正规训练。 3. There is only a formal resemblance between the two systems; they are in fact radically different. 这两种体系只是在表面上有某种相似之处，其实根本不同。 4. The writer made a formal denial of the hearsay. 这位作家公开否认了这一传闻。', '副词: formally 名词: formalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lurk', '[lɜːrk]', 'v.潜藏；潜伏；埋伏 n.潜伏；隐藏', '1. Danger lurked in the atmosphere. 氛围中隐藏着危险。 2. Dangers seem to lurk beneath this river. 这条河流潜藏许多危险。 3. The terrorists lurk in an apartment in downtown Copenhagen. 恐怖分子潜伏哥本哈根闹市区一处公寓。 4. The thief lurked in the shadows. 小偷埋伏在阴暗处。 5. The terrorists lurk in an apartment in downtown Copenhagen. 恐怖分子潜伏哥本哈根闹市区一处公寓。', '副词: lurkingly 过去式: lurked 过去分词: lurked 现在分词: lurking 第三人称单数: lurks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('panacea', '[ˌpænə\'siːə]', 'n.万灵药；灵丹妙药', '1. There\'s no single panacea for the country\'s economic ills. 国家经济弊病百出，并无万灵药可以医治。 2. It is not a panacea, but a stimulus to the economy is correct. 它不是什么万灵药，但给经济一个刺激是正确的。 3. Love is a panacea that cures spiritual wounds. 爱是一剂治疗心灵创伤的灵丹妙药。 4. Actually you have not taken any panacea and the tonic. 其实你没有吃过什么灵丹妙药和补品。', '形容词: panacean');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('convert', '[kən\'vɜːrt]', 'v.(使)转变；使…改变信仰；转化；兑换；换算 n.皈依者；改变信仰的人', '1. The solar cell can convert the energy of sunlight into electric energy. 太阳能电池能把阳光的能量转化为电能。 2. The old barn we bought to convert into flats was practically tumbling down. 那个旧谷仓我们买下想改建住房的，实际上已经快塌了。 3. My mother has converted to Catholicism. 我母亲已转而信仰天主教。 4. Coal can be converted to gas. 煤可以转化成煤气。 5. He is a recent convert to Christianity. 他最近改信基督教了。', '过去式: converted 过去分词: converted 现在分词: converting 第三人称单数: converts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('precipitate', '[prɪ\'sɪpɪteɪt]', 'vt.促成；使 ... 沉淀；猛摔 n.沉淀物；冷凝物 adj.仓促的；迅猛的；感情用事的', '1. All this will precipitate an economic crisis. 所有这些会促成经济危机。 2. It would only serve to precipitate his ruin. 它只会加速他的毁灭。 3. Iron and aluminum compounds precipitate as a voluminous sludge. 铁和铝的化合物成为一种体积庞大的蓬松的游渣沉淀下来。 4. The cart overturned and precipitated us to the ditch. 车子翻了，我们被摔进了沟里。 5. A yellow precipitate should form immediately. 很快会形成一种黄色沉淀物。 6. They made a precipitate decision. 他们作了一个轻率的决定。', '形容词: precipitative 副词: precipitately 名词: precipitateness 过去式: precipitated 过去分词: precipitated 现在分词: precipitating 第三人称单数: precipitates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dissimilar', '[dɪ\'sɪmɪlər]', 'adj.不同的', '1. All mating threaded parts are made of dissimilar,non-galling metals. 所有的螺纹配合件均采用不同的材质以避免互相咬死。 2. The process of imitation probably never commenced between forms widely dissimilar in colour. 色彩完全不同的类型之间，大概决不会有模仿过程发生。', '副词: dissimilarly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gentle', '[\'dʒentl]', 'adj.温和的；轻柔的；温顺的；文雅的；出身名门的', '1. We\'ve never met such gentle people. 我们从来没有遇到这样温和的人。 2. My mother is a kind and gentle woman. 我的母亲是一位心地善良、性情温和的妇女。 3. The gentle music can relax him. 轻柔的音乐能使他放松。 4. A gentle breeze stirred the leaves. 微风吹动了树叶。', '副词: gently 比较级: gentler 最高级: gentlest 名词: gentleness 过去式: gentled 过去分词: gentled 现在分词: gentling 第三人称单数: gentles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bind', '[baɪnd]', 'v.捆绑；装订；约束；强迫；团结 n.窘境', '1. She bound her hair with a handkerchief. 她用手绢把头发扎了起来。 2. This hint was hard enough to bind my hands. 这个暗示已经够使我束手无策了。 3. The publishing house decided to bind the new book in leather. 这家出版社决定用皮面装帧新书。 4. I am bound by my promise. 我必须遵守自己的诺言。 5. Their refusal to sign the contract has put us in a bit of a bind. 他们拒绝签约，从而使我们的处境有些困难。', '过去式: bound 过去分词: bound 现在分词: binding 第三人称单数: binds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resin', '[\'rezn]', 'n.树脂；松香；树脂制品 vt.涂树脂', '1. Amber is the resin of pine trees that grew very very long ago. 琥珀是古老的松脂。 2. They are made of a common plastic resin. 它们是用一种普通的塑胶合成树脂做成的。 3. From three o\'clock onward they would be burning resin. 从3点钟以后，它们就燃烧着松香。 4. This shelf was made of synthetic resin. 这个架子是合成树脂做的。', '形容词: resinous 过去式: resined 过去分词: resined 现在分词: resining 第三人称单数: resines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('belie', '[bɪ\'laɪ]', 'v.掩饰；与 ... 不符；使 ... 失望', '1. His cheerful manner belied his real feelings. 他那快活的样子掩饰了他真实的感情。 2. Practical experience belies this theory. 实际经验证明这个理论是错误的。 3. Yet his actions belie that agnosticism. 然而他却言行不一。', '名词: belier 过去式: belied 过去分词: belied 现在分词: belying 第三人称单数: belies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intermediary', '[ˌɪntər\'miːdieri]', 'n.仲裁者；调解者；中介 adj.中间的；媒介的 [计算机] 媒介.', '1. Explained by Gautama Buddha, he also stated that there is no intermediary between mankind and the divine; distant gods and God are subjected to karma themselves in decaying heavens. 佛陀解释，他也声称人与神之间并没有仲裁者；遥远的众神和神本身在腐朽的天堂上会受到因果报应。 2. He refused to act as an intermediary between the two director. 他拒绝充当这两个董事之间的调解人。 3. I found a part-time job through a intermediary. 我通过中介找到了一份兼职。 4. For Descartes, the imagination is a important intermediary between the thinking and the extension. 想象是思维转向物体性广延的重要中介。 5. Now, a living language has been found that can play the same intermediary role more successfully. 最近，已找到了一种现存的语言，它能更有效地起到中间媒介的作用。', '名词复数: intermediaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('innocent', '[\'ɪnəsnt]', 'adj.清白的；无害的；无辜的；无知的；天真纯洁的', '1. A man is accounted innocent until he is proven guilty. 一个人未被证明有罪前，被视为是清白的。 2. He was charged with murder but found innocent later. 他被控杀人，但后来发现他是无罪的。 3. It was an innocent deception, meant as a joke. 那是个无伤大雅的骗术，开个玩笑而已。 4. He declared that he was innocent. 他声称自己是无罪的。', '副词: innocently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('close', '[kloʊs]', 'v.关；合拢；不开放；停业；结束；收盘；（使）缩小；牢牢握住或抓住；（使）靠拢；同意；短兵相接 adj.亲近的；近的；几乎的；闷热的；严密的；紧凑的；剪得很短的；守口如瓶的；吝啬的；势均力敌的 adv.接近；靠近；紧紧地 n.死胡同；完结；结论', '1. If you close your eyes, you can\'t see anything. 如果你闭上眼睛，就什么也看不见了。 2. The road was closed to traffic for two days. 这条路已经封路两天了。 3. The hospital closed at the end of last year. 这所医院去年年底关闭。 4. He closed his speech with a funny joke. 他用一则有趣的笑话结束了演讲。 5. I believe you and he were very close friends. 我相信你和他是亲密无间的朋友。 6. They live quite close. 他们住得很近. 7. He soon brought the meeting to a close. 他很快就结束了会见。', '副词: closely 比较级: closer 最高级: closest 名词: closeness 过去式: closed 过去分词: closed 现在分词: closing 第三人称单数: closes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mediate', '[\'miːdieɪt]', 'v.调停；斡旋 adj.居间的；间接的', '1. He attempted to mediate their differences. 他试图调停他们的分歧。 2. He cooled the situation down by offering to mediate between the disputing parties. 他提出愿为争执的双方调停，情况因此缓和下来。 3. A well-known local lawyer has been appointed to mediate between the employers and the union leaders, since they can\'t reach an agreement in direct talks. 既然雇主们同工会领袖无法在直接谈判中达成协议，就指定了一位当地的名律师进行调解。 4. He tried to mediate between his colleagues and management. 他设法在同事和管理阶层之间斡旋。 5. There were some mediate contacts between the two countries before their diplomatic relation was established. 在两国外交关系建立之前, 已经有些间接的接触。', '副词: mediately 过去式: mediated 过去分词: mediated 现在分词: mediating 第三人称单数: mediates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cult', '[kʌlt]', 'n.宗教膜拜仪式；异教；狂热崇拜；个人崇拜', '1. The cult of the Virgin Mary was extremely popular. 对圣母马利亚的膜拜当时非常流行。 2. The cult of sun worship is probably the most primitive one. 太阳崇拜仪式或许是最为原始的一种。 3. So this cult has been causing all the trouble? 那么就是这邪教导致了一切的麻烦? 4. This is an essential feature of a cult. 这是邪教的一大特征。', '形容词: cultic 名词: cultism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laundry', '[\'lɔːndri]', 'n.洗衣店；洗衣；要洗的衣服', '1. Send these clothed over to the laundry. 把这些衣服送到洗衣店去洗。 2. This laundry makes deliveries on Thursday. 这个洗衣店星期四送衣服。 3. I\'d like to have laundry service. 我需要洗衣服务。 4. Why don\'t you help your mother do the laundry? 你为什么不帮你妈妈洗衣服?', '名词复数: laundries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hurdle', '[\'hɜːrdl]', 'n.栏干；障碍 [计算机] 障碍. vt.跨越某物', '1. I defy you to jump that high hurdle. 我倒要看看你能不能跳过那高栏。 2. His horse fell as it jumped the last hurdle. 他的马在跨跃最后一个跳栏时跌倒了。 3. Software may turn out to be a bigger hurdle. 软件可能成为更大的障碍。 4. You have to hurdle to London and get the intelligence back. 你得克服困难到达伦敦把那份情报取回来。', '名词: hurdler 过去式: hurdled 过去分词: hurdled 现在分词: hurdling 第三人称单数: hurdles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('uproar', '[\'ʌprɔːr]', 'n.骚动；喧嚣', '1. The exorbitant fees caused an uproar across the land. 高昂的收费在整个地区引起了一场骚动。 2. We remained under cover for about two months until the uproar subsided. 骚动平息之前，我们躲了将近两个月。 3. His motion threw the meeting into an uproar. 他的建议在会上引起了一片吵嚷。 4. The subsequent uproar ended the class. 接下来的喧嚣结束了那堂课。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sprawl', '[sprɔːl]', 'vi.躺卧；扩张；蔓延 vt.使蔓延 n.躺卧；蔓延', '1. Corporate sprawl distracts managers, diverts resources and muddies valuations. 公司扩张吸引管理层，转移资源和扰乱估价。 2. By designing new neighborhoods with pedestrians in mind, they can promote slimmer lifestyles and cut down on this new kind of suburban sprawl. 如果在规划设计时就能更多地考虑到步行的需要，就能促使人们采用更健康的生活方式，并遏制市郊的无限扩张。 3. Urban sprawl was essentially unplanned. 城市蔓延是生来无计划的。 4. Sprawl is common in the United States. 城市蔓延在美国非常普遍。 5. Urban sprawl was essentially unplanned. 城市蔓延是生来无计划的。 6. Urban sprawl was essentially unplanned. 城市蔓延是生来无计划的。', '名词: sprawler 过去式: sprawled 过去分词: sprawled 现在分词: sprawling 第三人称单数: sprawls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('joyous', '[\'dʒɔɪəs]', 'adj.充满快乐的；使人高兴的', '1. The poem is a joyous affirmation of the power of love. 这首诗以欢快的笔触肯定了爱情的力量。 2. The sudden bad news damped the joyous atmosphere. 突然传来的坏消息打破了快乐的气氛。 3. The music of this song sent her carefree and joyous. 这支歌的乐曲使她心旷神怡。 4. Yet contact between the dead and the living can be joyous. 但死者与生者之间的联络也可以是令人高兴的。', '副词: joyously 名词: joyousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delude', '[dɪ\'luːd]', 'v.欺骗；迷惑；蛊惑', '1. He deluded her with empty promises. 他用虚假的诺言哄骗了她。 2. She deluded herself with false hopes. 她以虚幻的希望欺骗自己。 3. You must not delude him into believing it. 你不可误导他相信那件事。 4. Candidates running for president often delude the voters with election promises. 参加总统竞选的候选人往往以竞选许诺来蛊惑选民。', '副词: deludingly 名词: deluder 过去式: deluded 过去分词: deluded 现在分词: deluding 第三人称单数: deludes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('coincide', '[ˌkoʊɪn\'saɪd]', 'vi.一致；同时发生；符合', '1. They didn\'t coincide in opinion. 他们的意见不统一。 2. Our opinions did not coincide on this case. 在这个案例上,我们的意见不一致。 3. My religious beliefs don\'t coincide with yours. 我的宗教信仰跟你的不一样。 4. Their stories coincided. 他们的叙述一致.', '过去式: coincided 过去分词: coincided 现在分词: coinciding 第三人称单数: coincides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('colonize', '[\'kɑːlənaɪz]', 'v.开拓殖民地；移居于殖民地', '1. Britain colonized many parts of Africa. 英国在非洲开拓了许多殖民地。 2. Some Westerners came to colonize; others came to convert; most came to exploit. 有些西方人为了殖民而来，有些是为了宣传基督教义，但大多数是为了剥削。 3. Someday human beings will attempt to colonize outer space. 有朝一日人类会试图开拓外太空成殖民地。 4. The divers want to show it\'s possible for humans to colonize the seabed. 这几名潜水员想证明人类能够在海底生活。', '名词: colonizer 过去式: colonized 过去分词: colonized 现在分词: colonizing 第三人称单数: colonizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circuitous', '[sər\'kjuːɪtəs]', 'adj.迂回的；绕行的', '1. The more circuitous route would be the quickest. 采取比较迂回的路线，可能是捷径。 2. Many alien plants have become introduced by highly circuitous routes. 许多外来植物是通过极其迂回曲折的道路引进的。 3. They took a circuitous route to avoid reporters. 他们绕道避开了记者。 4. We had to take a circuitous route because of an accident on the turnpike. 由于收费公路上发生了事故,我们不得不绕路走。', '副词: circuitously 名词: circuity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('squirt', '[skwɜːrt]', 'v.喷出；溅迸；注射 n.水枪；注射器；喷出', '1. If all else fails, the species can also squirt ink, like octopuses. 如果变色之后仍被敌人发现，它们则会像章鱼一样喷出墨液，并在墨液掩护下逃生。 2. In it spends to be generally American to squirt in the hole. 在从这个洞里喷出如花一般美的颜色。 3. When the operating medium contains some granules, you can squirt lotion or lubricant to clean the seal face, making sure a reliable seal. 当输送的介质不洁或含有少量颗粒时，为保护密封面，确保达到可靠的密封，还可给这一装置注射相应的清洗剂或润滑剂对密封面进行清洗。 4. The little boy wants to buy a squirt gun. 这个小男孩想买个水枪。', '名词: squirter 过去式: squirted 过去分词: squirted 现在分词: squirting 第三人称单数: squirts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mate', '[meɪt]', 'n.配偶；伙伴；同事 vt.使 ... 配对；使 ... 一致 vi.交配', '1. I thought she was an ideal mate. 我认为她是我的理想配偶。 2. The eagle mourned for his dead mate. 那只鹰为它死去的配偶伤心。 3. He is my soul mate. 他和我性情相投。 4. Who is your best mate at Liverpool? 谁是你在利物浦最好的伙伴? 5. It\'s high time to mate the doves. 现在正是鸽子配对的好时候。 6. Many animals mate in the spring. 许多动物在春天交配。', '过去式: mated 过去分词: mated 现在分词: mating 第三人称单数: mates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contagious', '[kən\'teɪdʒəs]', 'adj.传染性的；感染性的', '1. Scarlet fever is highly contagious. 猩红热传染性很强。 2. Have you ever had any contagious disease? 你是否有或曾经有过传染疾病? 3. The incidence of various contagious diseases has markedly dropped. 各种传染病的发病率大幅度下降。 4. He has contagious laughter. 他有着容易感染人的笑声。', '副词: contagiously 名词: contagiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intimacy', '[\'ɪntɪməsi]', 'n.亲密；隐私', '1. All the charm of their intimacy was gone. 他们之间那种亲密的闲情逸致也就此完了。 2. He exchanged intimacies with his bosom friend at the party. 在晚会上，他和他的密友亲密交谈。 3. If you plan openness, you will reap intimacy. 如果你种下坦率 4. He refused to tell it to me except in the intimacy of his room. 除非避开众人耳目在他房间里私下谈,否则他不肯把这件事告诉我。', '名词复数: intimacies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('potent', '[\'poʊtnt]', 'adj.强有力的；有效的', '1. We must take account of his potent influence. 我们必须考虑到他的强有力的影响。 2. I was convinced by his potent arguments. 他那有力的论据把我说服了。 3. Some narcotics are extraordinarily potent. 有些麻醉药的效力非常强。 4. The poison of the snake is a very potent. 那只蛇的毒很强。', '副词: potently 名词: potentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sake', '[seɪk]', 'n.理由；缘故；目的；利益', '1. He is away all year for the sake of his work. 因工作关系，他整年出门在外。 2. You should take care of your niece for the sake of your sister. 看在姐妹的份上，你应该照顾你的侄女。 3. Never do wrong for the sake of money. 绝不要为金钱而做坏事。 4. It\'s the company\'s policy to sacrifice short-term profits for the sake of long-term growth. 为长期发展而牺牲短期利润是公司的方针。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contemptuous', '[kən\'temptʃʊəs]', 'adj.轻视的；轻蔑的；瞧不起的', '1. You should not be contemptuous of underprivileged people. 你不应该看不起无权无势的人。 2. He gave a contemptuous laugh. 他轻蔑地笑了笑。 3. My girl friend is contemptuous of my humble home. 我的女朋友瞧不起我的简陋的家。 4. Snobs are usually contemptuous of people they feel to be beneath them. 势利者通常瞧不起他们认为地位在他们之下的人。', '副词: contemptuously 名词: contemptuousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circulate', '[\'sɜːrkjəleɪt]', 'vi.流通；循环；传播 vt.使流通，使环流', '1. Please open a window to allow the air to circulate. 打开窗子让空气流通。 2. Foreign money is not allowed to circulate in China. 外币不允许在中国流通。 3. Money shall circulate freely within the common market. 货币应在共同市场内自由流通。 4. Blood circulates through the body. 血液在体内循环。', '形容词: circulative 名词: circulator 过去式: circulated 过去分词: circulated 现在分词: circulating 第三人称单数: circulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oust', '[aʊst]', 'v.逐出；夺取；取代', '1. The umpire ousted the arguing player from the game. 裁判员将那位不服判决的运动员罚下场。 2. Fox was ousted from office but he had nothing to say for himself. 福克斯被赶下台，但是他没有什么可特别为自己辨护的。 3. The rebels finally managed to oust the government from power. 反叛者最后总算夺取了政权。 4. I \'m sorry to say nothing could oust a computer. 很遗憾，什么也不可能取代计算机。', '过去式: ousted 过去分词: ousted 现在分词: ousting 第三人称单数: ousts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recipe', '[\'resəpi]', 'n.秘诀；食谱；药方', '1. What\'s your recipe for success? 你取得成功有什么窍门？ 2. He knows the recipe for this dish. 他知道这道菜的烹饪方法。 3. This recipe will be enough for four servings. 本食谱为四人食用分量。 4. In fact, could I ask you for the recipe? 事实上,我能向你要这道菜的食谱吗?', '名词复数: recipes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('composure', '[kəm\'poʊʒər]', 'n.镇静；沉着', '1. Keep calm; don\'t lose your composure. 保持镇静，不要惊慌失措。 2. She recovered her composure and smiled. 她恢复了镇静，笑了笑。 3. He could see that she was struggling to preserve her composure. 他看出她是竭力故作镇定。 4. He showed great composure in difficult situations. 他在困难环境中表现得极沉着。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resonance', '[\'rezənəns]', 'n.共鸣；共振；反响', '1. His voice can produce a great resonance. 他的声音能发出深沉的共鸣声。 2. His words will have resonance for many musicians. 他的话引起了许多音乐家的共鸣。 3. Resonance would occur again, but not so strong as before. 共振会再次发生，但不如先前那么强。 4. Resonance is often observed in nature. 在自然界中,常常可以观察到共振现象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jeer', '[dʒɪr]', 'v.嘲弄；揶揄；奚落 n.嘲笑；讥评', '1. They all jeered at the foolish speaker. 他们都嘲笑那个愚蠢的演说者。 2. He jeered at the defeated opponent. 他揶揄着被击败的对手。 3. He was stabbed to the heart by the girl\'s jeer. 那女孩的嘲讽深深地刺伤了他的心。 4. He ran off,their jeers ringing in his ears. 他一跑了之', '副词: jeeringly 名词: jeerer 过去式: jeered 过去分词: jeered 现在分词: jeering 第三人称单数: jeers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invalid', '[ɪn\'vælɪd]', 'adj.无效的；病弱的 n.病人；残疾者 vt.退役；遣送回家', '1. A passport that is out of date is invalid. 护照过期是无效的。 2. Unless a check is signed, it is invalid. 支票除非签了名，否则是无效的。 3. She looks after her invalid mother. 她照看病弱的母亲。 4. Nobody looks after the invalid. 没人照顾这个病人。 5. He was invalided out of the army because of the wounds he received. 他因负伤而退役。', '副词: invalidly 名词: invalidity 过去式: invalided 过去分词: invalided 现在分词: invaliding 第三人称单数: invalids');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('academy', '[ə\'kædəmi]', 'n.学院；学会；专科学校', '1. He is a student in an academy of music. 他是一所音乐学院的学生。 2. He was expelled from the Academy of Sciences. 他被科学院开除了。 3. The Royal Academy is regarded as the sanctuary by artists. 英国皇家艺术学会被艺术家视为圣殿。 4. After graduating from Whittier Academy, my mother went on to Whittier College. 我母亲从惠蒂尔专科学校毕业后，进了惠蒂尔学院。', '名词复数: academies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('polygon', '[\'pɑːliɡɑːn]', 'n.多边形', '1. The following example draws a three-sided polygon. 下面的示例绘制了一个三条边的多边形。 2. On the other hand we could put the polygon in all cubes it is in. 还有，我们可以把一个多边形放在所有它所在的立方体里面。', '形容词: polygonal 副词: polygonally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('propensity', '[prə\'pensəti]', 'n.倾向；习性', '1. He showed a propensity for violence. 他表现出暴力倾向。 2. He has a propensity for drinking too much alcohol. 他有酗酒的倾向。 3. This view is based on the propensity of following points. 这个看法基于以下几点倾向。 4. She has a propensity to exaggerate. 她有夸大的习性。', '名词复数: propensities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('frame', '[freɪm]', 'n.骨架；身躯；结构；框；帧 v.表达；制定；把 ... 框起来；陷害', '1. She is having a lean, gaunt frame with prominent bones. 他骨瘦如柴的身材又细又瘦,骨骼突出的 2. Sobs shook her slender frame. 她抽泣著，苗条的身体都在颤动。 3. This athlete has a powerful frame. 这位运动员有着魁梧的体格。 4. It gives the frame of DFL programming language. 提出了DFL程序设计语言的基本框架结构。 5. His lips could hardly frame the words. 他几乎说不出话来。', '过去式: framed 过去分词: framed 现在分词: framing 第三人称单数: frames');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inhibit', '[ɪn\'hɪbɪt]', 'v.抑制；阻止；使不能', '1. You should inhibit wrong desires and impulses. 你应当抑制不正当的欲望和行动。 2. These compounds inhibit microbial growth. 这些化合物能抑制微生物的生长。 3. Why didn\'t you inhibit him from doing that? 为何你不阻止他做那种事? 4. They passed a law to inhibit people from parking in the street. 他们通过一项法令以阻止人们在街上停车。', '形容词: inhibitable 过去式: inhibited 过去分词: inhibited 现在分词: inhibiting 第三人称单数: inhibits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('musicologist', '[ˌmjuːzɪ\'kɒlədʒɪst]', 'n.音乐学者；音乐理论家', '1. She was married to critic and musicologist Aladar Toth (1898-1986); she is buried next to him in Budapest. 她嫁给了评论家和音乐阿拉达尔托特（1898至1986年）;她被安葬在他旁边的布达佩斯。 2. The musical analysis performed by OMRAS is unlike any that a musicologist would recognise. “快变”及其类似产品的工作原理都是将声音和几百万首储存在一个中央数据库中的录音资料加以匹配。 3. Profession (e.g. composer, musicologist, performer, etc. Performers please state instruments. 专业(例如:作曲家;音乐家;演奏家等等.;演奏家请注明演奏乐器 4. An eminent musicologist, mathematician and calendarist, who was honored to be “oriental personage of artistic encyclopedia type”. 明代杰出乐律家、算学家和历学家，被西方赞誉为“东方百科艺术全书式的人物”。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('photosynthesis', '[ˌfoʊtoʊ\'sɪnθəsɪs]', 'n.光合作用', '1. Photosynthesis is an endergonic process. 光合作用是吸收能量的过程。 2. Our current research topic is photosynthesis. 我们现在研究的课题是光合作用。 3. Plants absorb solar energy during photosynthesis. 植物通过光合作用吸收太阳能。', '形容词: photosynthetic 副词: photosynthetically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('array', '[ə\'reɪ]', 'n.一系列；大批；数组；陈列，列队；盛装 vt.排列；部署；打扮', '1. The era also gave birth to a whole array of new social problems. 那个时代还产生了一系列新的社会问题。 2. We have quite an array of leather shoes. 我们有一大批各类皮鞋。 3. Today\'s vehicles offer an array of advanced safety features. 现在的汽车都提供了大量先进的安全设备。 4. Our troops were drawn up in battle array. 我们的部队已严阵以待。 5. I want to array this specimen mount in the display window. 我想把这个标本架放到橱窗里。', '过去式: arrayed 过去分词: arrayed 现在分词: arraying 第三人称单数: arrays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conservative', '[kən\'sɜːrvətɪv]', 'adj.保守的；守旧的 n.保守派(党)；保守的人', '1. He was very conservative in the estimate. 他的这一估计很保守。 2. Old people are usually more conservative than young people. 老年人通常比年轻人保守。 3. The professor\'s a radical in politics but a conservative dresser. 教授在政治上是激进派,但衣着却很守旧。 4. The man turned from Radical to Conservative. 这人从激进派变成了保守派。', '副词: conservatively 名词: conservativeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deferential', '[ˌdefə\'renʃl]', 'adj.恭敬的；顺从的', '1. He is deferential to his superiors. 他对他的长官是恭敬的。 2. She is always extremely deferential to anyone in authority. 她对任何权威人士总是必恭必敬。', '副词: deferentially');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('contain', '[kən\'teɪn]', 'vt.容纳；包含；抑制；克制 vi.自制', '1. The atlas contains forty maps. 这个地图集有四十幅地图。 2. Does each cup contain the same amount of milk? 每个杯子里的牛奶都一样多吗? 3. This book contains all the information you need. 这本书包含你所需的一切资料。 4. I could hardly contain my curiosity. 我简直无法克制我的好奇心 5. She couldn\'t contain herself for joy. 她高兴地难以自制。', '形容词: containable 过去式: contained 过去分词: contained 现在分词: containing 第三人称单数: contains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conscientious', '[ˌkɒnʃɪ\'enʃəs]', 'adj.认真的；谨慎的；负责的', '1. The janitor is very conscientious. 那个管理员很认真。 2. He\'s changed into a conscientious worker. 他已成为一个工作认真的人了。 3. Be more conscientious about your work. 要更谨慎做你的工作。 4. This essay is a most conscientious piece of work. 这篇论文是精雕细刻的工作.', '副词: conscientiously 名词: conscientiousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dread', '[dred]', 'v.惧怕；担心 n.恐惧；可怕的人或事 adj.恐怖的；使人敬畏的', '1. I dread having to visit the dentist . 我害怕看牙医。 2. I dread to think what will happen if she finds out the truth. 我不敢去想她知道真相后会怎么样。 3. Much of what we dread is really due to indistinctness of outline. 畏生于不明，大抵如此。 4. The Jews lived in dread of being caught. 这些犹太人生活在会遭到拘捕的恐惧之中。 5. The countryside lay as under some dread enchantment. 乡村好像躺在某种可怖的魔法之下。', '过去式: dreaded 过去分词: dreaded 现在分词: dreading 第三人称单数: dreads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('combine', '[kəm\'baɪn]', 'v.联合；使结合；结合 n.集团；联合收割机；联合企业', '1. Two parties will combine to defeat the third. 两党派将联合以击败第三党。 2. We can\'t always combine work with pleasure. 我们并不总是能在工作中享受到乐趣。 3. He combines creative imagination and true scholarship. 他同时具有创造性想象力和真正的治学谨严学风。 4. We should combine work with rest. 我们应劳逸结合。 5. The newspaper combine threatened all the smaller papers. 这家报刊集团威胁者小报社的生存。', '名词: combiner 过去式: combined 过去分词: combined 现在分词: combining 第三人称单数: combines');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mint', '[mɪnt]', 'n.薄荷；造币厂；<口>巨额 vt.铸造(硬币)；伪造 adj.完美无缺的', '1. Sage, mint and dill are all herbs. 鼠尾草、 薄荷、 莳萝均为药草。 2. He put the sugar, mint and a little soda into a tall tumbler. 他在一只高脚杯子中加了糖、薄荷和一点苏打水。 3. The Royal Mint will strike a commemorative gold coin. 英国皇家造币厂将铸造一种纪念金币。 4. Father left him a mint of money. 父亲留给他一大笔钱。 5. The Romans learned to mint from the Greeks. 罗马人从希腊人那里学会了铸造钱币。', '形容词: minty 名词: minter 过去式: minted 过去分词: minted 现在分词: minting 第三人称单数: mints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beset', '[bɪ\'set]', 'vt.包围；困扰；镶嵌', '1. Buck was beset by three huskies, and in a trice his head and shoulders were ripped and slashed. 三只赫斯基狗包围了巴克，瞬息间便咬破了他的头和肩膀。 2. The country was beset with many problems. 这个国家被许多困难所困扰。 3. But a new threat faces a population already beset by hardship. 但这些已经被困境困扰的人民还面临着新的威胁。 4. The crown was beset with diamonds and jewels. 皇冠上镶嵌着钻石和珠宝。', '名词: besetment 过去式: beset 过去分词: beset 现在分词: besetting 第三人称单数: besets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('depart', '[dɪ\'pɑːrt]', 'vt.离开 vi.离开；死亡', '1. He departed this life at the age of seventy. 他70岁时去世。 2. I\'ll depart Washington for London tomorrow 我明天将离开华盛顿前往伦敦。 3. He seemed somewhat loath to depart. 他似乎不愿离去。 4. The train to Beijing will depart from platform 3 in half an hour. 开往北京的火车将于半小时后从三站台开出。', '过去式: departed 过去分词: departed 现在分词: departing 第三人称单数: departs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('morale', '[mə\'ræl]', 'n.士气；斗志；道德准则', '1. They bolstered their morale by singing. 他们以唱歌来鼓舞士气。 2. They sang songs to keep their morale up. 他们唱　歌以保持高昂的士气。 3. We\'ll soon attack the enemy together. Keep up your morale, soldier! 我们就要会剿敌军了，同志们要保持斗志啊。 4. A sincere compliment boosts one\'s morale. 由衷的称赞可鼓舞一个人的精神。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attractive', '[ə\'træktɪv]', 'adj.有吸引力的；有魅力的', '1. Ice-cream is attractive to children. 冰淇淋对孩子们非常有吸引力。 2. It\'s an attractive idea. 这是个使人感兴趣的想法。 3. It\'s a very attractive offer, and I\'m tempted to accept. 这项建议很有吸引力,我确实有些动心。 4. I think she is a very attractive girl. 我认为她是很有魅力的女孩。', '副词: attractively 名词: attractiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conclude', '[kən\'kluːd]', 'vt.推断出；缔结；使结束 vi.结束；总结；作决定；作协议', '1. From his appearance we may safely conclude that he is a chain smoker. 从他的外表，我们可以有把握地断定他烟抽得很凶。 2. The two countries are reported to have concluded a military convention. 据报导,这两个国家已缔结军事协定。 3. He conclude the negotiation with dispatch. 他迅速结束谈判。 4. The concert concluded with the National Anthem. 音乐会最后以演奏国歌结束。', '名词: concluder 过去式: concluded 过去分词: concluded 现在分词: concluding 第三人称单数: concludes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dissipate', '[\'dɪsɪpeɪt]', 'v.驱散；消散；散去；浪费；挥霍；放荡', '1. The sun dissipated the mist. 太阳驱散了雾。 2. Her son\'s letter dissipated all her fears and anxiety. 她儿子的来信消除了她一切恐惧和焦虑。 3. The crowd dissipated soon after the police arrived. 在警察到达之后，人群很快散去了。 4. He soon dissipated his fortune. 他很快就把财产浪费光了。', '形容词: dissipative 名词: dissipater 过去式: dissipated 过去分词: dissipated 现在分词: dissipating 第三人称单数: dissipates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cube', '[kjuːb]', 'n.立方体；立方 vt.求 ... 的立方 adj.立方的', '1. A cube is a three-dimensional object. 立方体是三维物体。 2. Three cubed is twenty-seven. 三的立方是二十七。 3. If you cube 1 0 , the result is 1 0 0 0 . 如果你求10的立方，得出的结果是1000。 4. The National Aquatic Center is also called \"water cube \". 国家游泳中心又被称为“水立方”。', '名词: cuber 过去式: cubed 过去分词: cubed 现在分词: cubing 第三人称单数: cubes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('exposition', '[ˌekspə\'zɪʃn]', 'n.博览会；展览会；说明', '1. They are going to hold an international exposition. 他们打算召开一次国际博览会。 2. So the West Lake Exposition has a long history. 那西湖博览会已有很长的历史了。 3. He entered a landscape painting in the Exposition. 他把一幅风景画送展览会展出。 4. The World Exposition is not the same as a trade fair, in which mainly governments and international organizations participate. 世博会不同于贸易展览会，贸易展览会主要是由政府和国际组织参加的。', '形容词: expositive 名词: expositor');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('altruism', '[\'æltruɪzəm]', 'n.利他主义；利他', '1. Anonymity is the truest expression of altruism. 不记名是利他主义最真的表现。 2. Altruism, according to the text books, has two forms. 根据书本上的解释，利他主义有两种表现形式。 3. His altruism won the neighbors\' respect. 他那利他的行为赢得了邻居的尊敬。 4. Ambitionthat is masked as altruism. 利他主义掩盖下的野心。', '形容词: altruistic 副词: altruistically 名词: altruist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('facade', '[fə\'sɑːd]', 'n.建筑物的正面；外表(犹指虚伪的)', '1. That is the facade of the Palace. 那是宫殿的正面。 2. The figure belongs to one of the colossi of the facade. 该头像属于神殿正面的一尊巨像。 3. His fine clothes are a mere facade. 他漂亮的衣着只是虚有其表而已。 4. Squalor and poverty lay behind the city\'s glittering facade. 这城市表面繁华,背后却肮脏和贫困。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intersect', '[ˌɪntər\'sekt]', 'v.贯穿；(和 ... )相交；交叉', '1. The plain is intersected by a network of canals. 一个运河网络贯穿这片平原。 2. These two fences intersect at the creek. 这两片篱笆在一条羊肠小道相交。 3. The two roads intersect at the suburb of the city. 两条路在城郊交叉。 4. Streets usually intersect at right angles. 马路通常以直角交叉。', '过去式: intersected 过去分词: intersected 现在分词: intersecting 第三人称单数: intersects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flush', '[flʌʃ]', 'v.冲洗；发红；将某人赶出 n.脸红；冲洗；（纸牌）同花牌；【计算机】冲洗', '1. Father asked me to flush off the garage floor. 父亲叫我冲洗车库的地板。 2. The toilet won\'t flush properly. 马桶不好冲。 3. Don\'t forget to flush the toilet after use. 用完厕所,不要忘了冲。 4. Mary flushed crimson with embarrassment. 玛丽羞得脸红了。 5. A flush of excitement crept into his face. 兴奋的红晕爬上他的脸。', '比较级: flusher 最高级: flushest 名词: flusher 过去式: flushed 过去分词: flushed 现在分词: flushing 第三人称单数: flushes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spinning', '[\'spɪnɪŋ]', 'n.纺纱；(用旋式诱饵)钓鱼；一种运动 动词spin的现在分词形式.', '1. She is unbred to spinning. 她未受纺织之训练。 2. She is skilled at spinning and weaving. 她是纺织能手。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('energetic', '[ˌenər\'dʒetɪk]', 'adj.精力旺盛的；有力的；能量的', '1. His son is an energetic child. 他的儿子是个精力旺盛的孩子。 2. He seems an energetic person. 他似乎是一个精力充沛的人。 3. Her wiry athletic body seems energetic. 她瘦长结实的身体看上去精力充沛。 4. We should give energetic support to agriculture. 我们要大力支援农业。', '副词: energetically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('physical', '[\'fɪzɪkl]', 'adj.物质的；身体的；体力的；物理的；肉体上的，身体上的 <美>体格检查', '1. It\'s a physical impossibility to be in two places at one time. 同时在两地是自然规律上不可能的事。 2. Physical disability causes mental anguish. 生理伤残会引起心理苦闷。 3. Staying up late makes him at his worst in terms of physical situation. 熬夜使得他的体力状况处于低潮。 4. For them, getting rid of heavy physical labour is a big thing 对他们来说, 摆脱重体力劳动是一件大事。', '副词: physically 名词: physicality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('involve', '[ɪn\'vɑːlv]', 'vt.包含；使忙于；牵涉；使卷入；使陷入', '1. A letter of credit will involve unnecessary extra charges. 信用证包含有不必要的额外开支。 2. The Genius is a lovable physicist who is deeply involved in defining the workings of the universe. 老天才是一位可爱的学者，他整天忙于解释天地间的各种现象。. 3. Don\'t involve other people in your trouble. 别把别人牵涉进你的麻烦中去。 4. I got involved in a quarrel about the price. 我被卷入了一场有关价格的争吵。', '名词: involvement 过去式: involved 过去分词: involved 现在分词: involving 第三人称单数: involves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('feminist', '[\'femənɪst]', 'n.女权主义者 adj.主张男女平等的；女权主义的', '1. She is a card-carrying feminist. 她是典型的女权主义者。 2. A lot of people\'s eyes glaze over if you say you are a feminist. 如果你说你是女权主义者，好多人都会愣住。 3. She is a card-carrying feminist. 她是典型的女权主义者。 4. A lot of people\'s eyes glaze over if you say you are a feminist. 如果你说你是女权主义者，好多人都会愣住。', '形容词: feministic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pulp', '[pʌlp]', 'n.果肉；纸浆；木髓；牙髓；低级刊物 v.使成为浆状；除去 ... 的果肉；把...制成纸浆', '1. A banana is mainly pulp, except for its skin. 香蕉除了果皮之外，主要是果肉。 2. The pulp of mango tastes very sweet and soft. 芒果的果肉尝起来很甜且很软。 3. A thin film formed on the surface of the pulp. 纸浆表面结了一层膜。 4. Critics reviled the novel as unsophisticated pulp. 批评家把这部小说贬为不成熟的低级品。 5. Their feet have pulped the wet mud to a mire. 他们的脚把湿泥踩成了泥潭。', '形容词: pulpous 名词: pulpiness 过去式: pulped 过去分词: pulped 现在分词: pulping 第三人称单数: pulps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discernible', '[dɪ\'sɜːrnəbəl]', 'adj.可辨别的', '1. His face was barely discernible in the gloom. 在黑暗中很难看得清他的脸。 2. Recurring themes are readily discernible in the annals of history . 在历史纪录上完全可以找到重复的主题。', '副词: discernibly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('peculiar', '[pɪ\'kjuːliər]', 'adj.奇怪的；特殊的；独特的；古怪的 n.特权', '1. Did you notice anything peculiar? 你注意到有什么异常的事吗？ 2. The food has a peculiar taste. 这食物有种怪味道。 3. A peculiar feeling came over Feliks. 一种特殊的情感传遍费利克斯全身。 4. This actor has a peculiar charm, which attracts middle-aged women. 这个演员有种特殊的魅力，吸引了很多中年女性。 5. It\'s the manager\'s peculiar to use this meeting room. 使用这间会议室是经理的特权。', '副词: peculiarly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('distinguish', '[dɪ\'stɪŋɡwɪʃ]', 'vt.区别；辨认；使显著', '1. Speeches distinguish human beings from animals. 人类和动物的区别在于人会说话。 2. It\'s important to distinguish fact from fiction. 把现实与虚构区分开来是很重要的。 3. The twins were so much alike that it was impossible to distinguish one from the other. 这对孪生子像得使人无法分辨。 4. We should distinguish between right and wrong. 我们应辨别是非。', '形容词: distinguishable 副词: distinguishably 过去式: distinguished 过去分词: distinguished 现在分词: distinguishing 第三人称单数: distinguishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bundle', '[\'bʌndl]', 'n.捆；束；包；大笔钱 v.捆；把 ... 扎成一捆；匆忙地走', '1. He collected a bundle of sticks. 他收集了一捆树枝。 2. I see a bundle of firewood on the floor. 我看见了一捆劈柴在地板上。 3. On the table there is a bundle of flower. 桌子上有一束花。 4. My uncle sent me a large bundle on my birthday. 我生日时叔父给我寄来一个大包裹。 5. Can you bundle up the sheets for me? 你能替我将这些单子捆起来吗?', '名词: bundler 过去式: bundled 过去分词: bundled 现在分词: bundling 第三人称单数: bundles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('splendid', '[\'splendɪd]', 'adj.极好的；辉煌的；壮观的；杰出的', '1. Playing tabletennis is a splendid sport. 打乒乓球是极好的运动。 2. My kid sister has a splendid memory. 我小妹记忆力极好。 3. We won another splendid victory. 我们又赢得了辉煌的胜利。 4. The royal couple appeared in splendid array. 王室伉俪身穿盛装出现。', '副词: splendidly 名词: splendidness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('consensus', '[kən\'sensəs]', 'n.一致；同意；共识', '1. The two parties have reached a consensus. 这两个政党达成了一致意见。 2. It would be a good idea to predict which proposal is most likely to achieve consensus. 不妨研究一下哪项提案最有可能获得一致同意。 3. Yet the events of the past two years have called that consensus in question. 然而,过去两年来发生的各种事件使人们对这一共识产生了疑虑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('symbolic', '[sɪm\'bɒlɪk]', 'adj.象征的；符号的 n.代号', '1. It is highly philosophical and symbolic. 其中蕴涵着深刻的哲理和丰富的象征。 2. A wedding ring is usually a symbolic gesture of love. 结婚戒指通常是爱情象征的表示。 3. Dreams of ill health can be either literal or symbolic warnings. 生病的梦会是真正的或象征的警告。 4. The power of the monarchy in britain today is more symbolical than real. 今日英国君主的权力多为象征性的，无甚实际意义。', '副词: symbolically 异体字: symbolical 名词: symbolicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chore', '[tʃɔːr]', 'n.讨厌的工作；琐事；家务', '1. She finds shopping a chore. 她认为买东西是烦人的事。 2. It\'s such a chore to change diapers. 换尿布真是一件讨厌的事。 3. Shopping isn\'t a chore, it\'s recreation. 购物不是一件琐事，而是休闲。 4. All this was done to relieve women of household chores. 这一切都是为了把妇女从家务劳动中解放出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('teem', '[tiːm]', 'v.充满；富于；把……倒空；倾泻', '1. The river teems with all kinds of fish in summer. 夏天这条河里各种各样的鱼多得很。 2. The rain teemed down for hours. 大雨一直下了好几个小时。', '副词: teemingly 名词: teemer 过去式: teemed 过去分词: teemed 现在分词: teeming 第三人称单数: teems');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overlook', '[ˌoʊvər\'lʊk]', 'v.俯瞰；远眺；没注意到；忽视 n.忽视；远眺', '1. My room overlooked the garden. 我的房间俯瞰花园。 2. We overlook the church from our house. 我们可从家中俯瞰教堂。 3. My room overlooks the sea. 从我的房间可眺望大海。 4. He overlooked a spelling error on the first page. 他没有看出第一页中有个拼写错误。 5. It was a slight overlook on my part. 这是我的小疏忽。', '过去式: overlooked 过去分词: overlooked 现在分词: overlooking 第三人称单数: overlooks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enact', '[ɪ\'nækt]', 'vt.制定法律；扮演', '1. Several bills were enacted at the end of this session of Parliament. 这届国会结束时，好几个议案制定成为法律。 2. Our government has to enact better safety regulations in factories. 我们的政府应该要制定较好的工厂安全法规。 3. Americans are called to enact this promise in our lives and in our laws. 美国人民肩负着一种使命，那就是要竭力将这个诺言变成生活中和法律上的现实。 4. And then we enact one of my cunning rescue operations. 随后我们就会上演我那巧妙的营救行动了。', '形容词: enactable 名词: enactor 过去式: enacted 过去分词: enacted 现在分词: enacting 第三人称单数: enacts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('custom', '[\'kʌstəm]', 'n.习惯；风俗；惯例 （复）Customs: 海关；关税 adj.定做的；定制的', '1. The custom has now become a rule. 那种习惯现已变为成规。 2. It is my custom to go for a walk before breakfast. 早餐前出去散散步是我的习惯。 3. Custom rules the law. [谚]风俗左右法律。 4. The custom prevails over the whole area. 这风俗存在于这整个地区。 5. It took us only a few minutes to get through the Customs. 我们的海关检查只花了几分钟时间。 6. Please enter a name for the custom controller. 请输入自定义控制器的名称。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('divulge', '[daɪ\'vʌldʒ]', 'v.泄露；暴露', '1. He swore never to divulge the secret. 他立誓决不泄露秘密。 2. None of them would divulge the winner from last season. 他们中没有人会泄露上个赛季的冠军。 3. But in today\'s era of dating, you can\'t afford to divulge too much about where you work or where you hang out, as well. 但在当今的约会中，你无法承受过多的暴露你的工作地点或你经常去的地方所可能带来的后果。', '名词: divulgence 过去式: divulged 过去分词: divulged 现在分词: divulging 第三人称单数: divulges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('issue', '[\'ɪʃuː]', 'n.议题；问题；期刊号；一次发行额；发行；<律>子女 v.发表；公布；正式发给；发行；流出', '1. You\'re just avoiding the issue. 你只不过是在回避问题。 2. The union plans to raise the issue of overtime. 工会打算提出加班的问题。 3. Parliament will debate the nationalization issue next week. 议会将在下周辩论国有化议题。 4. They make an issue of this with UEFA. 他们就此向欧足联提出上诉。 5. Xinhua News Agency is authorized to issue the following statement. 新华社受权发表如下声明。', '形容词: issueless 名词: issuer 过去式: issued 过去分词: issued 现在分词: issuing 第三人称单数: issues');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proponent', '[prə\'poʊnənt]', 'n.提倡者；支持者', '1. He certainly would not be a proponent of big government. 他当然也不会成为大政体的一个部分。 2. McCain is a leading proponent of President Bush\'s troop surge strategy in an effort to quell sectarian violence. 麦凯恩是布什总统增兵平息宗教暴乱政策的主要建议者。 3. He later became a Member of Parliament and an ardent proponent of Irish independence. 此后，他成为英国国会议员，并成为爱尔兰独立运动的积极支持者。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('smother', '[\'smʌðər]', 'v.窒息；闷死；用沙等闷住火；忍住；厚厚地或大面积地覆盖', '1. They smother his better instinct. 这些声音窒息了他的良知。 2. He smothered the baby with a pillow. 他用枕头把婴儿闷死了。 3. It\'s better to smother the fire with the earth. 最好用土把火掩熄。 4. Smother the flames from the burning pan with a wet towel. 用湿毛巾把锅里的火扑灭。', '过去式: smothered 过去分词: smothered 现在分词: smothering 第三人称单数: smothers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kernel', '[\'kɜːrnl]', 'n.核心；仁；中心；精髓', '1. We must get at the kernel of the problem. 我们必须抓住问题的核心。 2. Are kernels of apricots edible? 杏仁能吃吗？ 3. The monitoring center is the kernel part of a home-oriented telemonitoring system.Its performance has influence on the tele-monitoring system definitively. 本文开发的中心监护站软件是远程家庭多生理参数监护系统的重要组成部分，其性能直接关系到远程监护系统的总体性能。 4. Mathematical thought and method is the kernel of mathematical knowledge. 数学思想方法是数学知识的精髓。', '形容词: kerneled');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vertical', '[\'vɜːrtɪkl]', 'adj.垂直的；纵向的；顶点的 n.垂直物；垂直的位置', '1. The northern face of the mountain is almost vertical. 这座山向北的一面几乎是垂直的。 2. The vertical line meets the horizontal one here. 垂直线与水平线在此相交。 3. Wire saws can cut in any orientation, vertical or horizontal. 钢丝锯能够切割任何方向,纵向或横向。 4. The angles refer to the polar view angle, i.e. the angle measured from the vertical. 角涉及到极面观的角，例如垂直物上测量的角。', '副词: vertically 名词: verticality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scope', '[skoʊp]', 'n.机会；范围；眼界；观看的仪器 vt.仔细研究', '1. He gets a work that gives scope for his abilities. 他得到了一份有机会发挥他才能的工作。 2. He has no scope for his particular talents. 他没有施展自己特殊才能的机会。 3. It is within my scope. 那是在我的范围之内。 4. This subject is outside the scope of our inquiry. 这个问题不在我们探讨的范围之内。 5. He scopes the big picture of Israeli-Arab relations. 他认真地查看关于以色列和阿拉伯关系的大图片。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meek', '[miːk]', 'adj.温顺的；谦恭的', '1. It is Mrs. White that makes the decisions in that family, not her meek little husBand. 那家庭决定事情的是怀特太太，不是她那温顺的小个子丈夫。', '副词: meekly 比较级: meeker 最高级: meekest');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blunt', '[blʌnt]', 'adj.钝的；迟钝的；直率的 v.使迟钝；变钝', '1. Blunt scissors don\'t cut cleanly. 钝剪刀剪不齐。 2. My pencil is blunt, could you lend me a knife to sharpen it? 我的铅笔钝了，你能借我把刀子削一削吗？ 3. It involves systematic yet banal design, and blunt reportage. 它使用系统的，然而平庸的设计和迟钝的新闻报道。 4. He\'s very blunt and will tell you what he thinks about anything. 他的个性非常直率,会把他所想的都说出来。 5. His mind was blunted by boredom. 他的头脑因厌烦而变得迟钝。', '副词: bluntly 比较级: blunter 最高级: bluntest 名词: bluntness 过去式: blunted 过去分词: blunted 现在分词: blunting 第三人称单数: blunts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reception', '[rɪ\'sepʃn]', 'n.接待；反应；接待处；欢迎；接收；招待会', '1. The bridal suite was prepared for the reception of the honeymooners. 新婚套间已准备好以接待度蜜月的人。 2. The play got a favourable reception from the critics. 该剧获评论界好评。 3. Wait for me at reception. 在接待处等我吧。 4. The bridal suite was prepared for the reception of the honeymooners. 新婚套间已准备好以接待度蜜月的人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enthrall', '[ɪn\'θrɔːl]', 'v.迷住；迷惑；奴役', '1. Such trends do not enthrall neutrals, many of whom would prefer to see free-scoring Barcelona win tomorrow. 这些趋势并没有迷惑住中立者，他们中的很多人更愿意火力十足的巴萨明天赢球。 2. They should have been noticed, but a wizard who could enthrall an army of abyssal beasts could delude a few pilots and guards, especially the night after Fleetswake. 他们应该已经被注意到，但一个能奴役深渊野兽大军的法师，自然也能迷惑几个领航员和守卫了，特别是在舰队尾波节的夜里。 3. They should have been noticed, but a wizard who could enthrall an army of abyssal beasts could delude a few pilots and guards, especially the night after Fleetswake. 他们应该已经被注意到，但一个能奴役深渊野兽大军的法师，自然也能迷惑几个领航员和守卫了，特别是在舰队尾波节的夜里。', '副词: enthrallingly 异体字: inthrall 名词: enthrallment 过去式: enthralled 过去分词: enthralled 现在分词: enthralling 第三人称单数: enthralls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ease', '[iːz]', 'n.容易；悠闲；安逸；自在 v.减轻；放松；缓和；缓慢移动', '1. He passed the test with ease. 他轻而易举地考及格了。 2. He is expected to win the game with ease. 预计他在比赛中会轻易获胜。 3. My parents are retired and now live a life of ease. 我的父母都退休了，现在过着安闲舒适的生活。 4. She is a rich woman now, and leads a life of ease. 她现在是个富婆,过着安逸的生活。 5. The pain began to ease up after she was given a sedative. 给她吃了一片镇痛药后,她的疼痛开始减轻。', '过去式: eased 过去分词: eased 现在分词: easing 第三人称单数: eases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('statistical', '[stə\'tɪstɪkl]', 'adj.统计的；统计学的', '1. It represents a statistical law. 它只是代表了一个统计的规律。 2. The analyst\'s judgement then must override mathematical and statistical significance. 分析家的判断必须超越数学和统计的有效性。 3. This is not intended to serve as a text of statistical techniques. 这并不是想把它变成统计学的技术课本。 4. The sample size in most deployments of Bollinger Bands is simply too small for statistical significance. 为统计学的意义在布林线的大多数推广的样品尺寸简单地是太小的。', '副词: statistically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spun', '[spʌn]', '动词spin的过去式和过去分词形式', '1. She spun round to catch the ball. 她飞快地转身接球。 2. He spun us this unlikely yarn about being trapped for hours in a broken lift. 他对我们胡诌在坏电梯中困了几个小时。 3. The little paper boat was caught in an eddy and spun round and round in the water. 小纸船卷进了漩涡中，在水中直打转。 4. The beggar spun a long yarn about his misfortunes. 那个乞丐编造了一大篇自己如何遭遇不幸的故事。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('manifold', '[\'mænɪfoʊld]', 'n.多种；复印本；多支管 adj.多种的；多方面的 v.复写；繁殖；增多', '1. The uses of this machine are manifold. 这台机器有多种用途。 2. Taoyuan Coal Mine is the threatened mine by manifold groundwater. 桃园煤矿是一个受多种地下水害威胁的矿井。 3. Interconnecting flow passages travel through the manifold from the valve cavities. 互相连接流程通道旅行过来自活瓣洞的复印本。 4. observant fairly', '副词: manifoldly 名词: manifoldness 过去式: manifolded 过去分词: manifolded 现在分词: manifolding 第三人称单数: manifolds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('influx', '[\'ɪnflʌks]', 'n.流入；河口；汇集；涌入', '1. This influx of money could be exaggerating the market\'s gyrations. 大量资金的流入会夸大市场的回旋余地。 2. The country simply cannot absorb this influx of refugees. 这个国家实在没有能力接纳这么多涌入的难民。 3. There was a sudden influx of goods onto the market. 大批商品一下子涌入市场。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('catching', '[\'kætʃɪŋ]', 'adj.易传染的；有魅力的；迷人的 n.捕捉 动词catch的现在分词形式.', '1. Their lively spirit is very catching. 她们高涨的情绪非常具有感染力。 2. Bad colds are catching. 恶性感冒是有传染性的。 3. Her eyes are the most catching I have ever seen. 她的眼睛是我见到过的最迷人的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('psychoanalysis', '[ˌsaɪkoʊə\'næləsɪs]', 'n.心理分析', '1. Freud is the inventor of psychoanalysis. 弗洛伊德是精神分析学说的创立者。 2. Because hypnosis is not anything new, it is far older than Freudian psychoanalysis. 因为催眠并不是什么新鲜玩意，它比弗洛伊德的精神分析学要久远的多。', '形容词: psychoanalytic 副词: psychoanalytically 名词: psychoanalyst 名词复数: psychoanalyses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deliberately', '[dɪ\'lɪbərətli]', 'adv.故意地；不慌不忙地', '1. You have deliberately acted against my wishes. 你故意和我的想法对著干。 2. He\'s being deliberately obtuse. 他装糊涂。 3. She had deliberately shifted our relations. 她故意地改变了我们的关系。 4. She continued deliberately to toss the books severally upon the floor. 她继续不紧不慢把书一本一本地往地上扔。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diameter', '[daɪ\'æmɪtər]', 'n.直径', '1. The diameter of the tree-trunk is about 2 meters. 这树干的直径大约是2米。 2. We must gauge the diameter of wire first. 我们必须先测量电线的直径。 3. The axis of a circle is its diameter. 圆的轴线是其直径。', '形容词: diametral');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elevate', '[\'elɪveɪt]', 'vt.举起；提拔；素养提升；鼓舞 vi.变高', '1. They had the attempt to elevate Anderson to the presidency. 他们企图把安德逊抬上总统宝座。 2. He used a couple of bolsters to elevate his head. 他用两个垫枕垫头。 3. They had the attempt to elevate Anderson to the presidency. 他们企图把安德逊抬上总统宝座。 4. Reading good books elevates your mind. 阅读好书使人思想高尚。', '过去式: elevated 过去分词: elevated 现在分词: elevating 第三人称单数: elevates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('span', '[spæn]', 'n.时期；跨度；间距 vt.延续；横跨；贯穿；遍及；弥补 动词spin的过去式形式.', '1. Modern medicine has increased man\'s life span. 现代医学延长了人的寿命。 2. He has settled here for a long span of time. 他已经在这儿定居很长一段时间了。 3. The arch has a span of 60 meters. 拱门的跨度为60米。 4. The spider has a leg span of 3 inches. 这个蜘蛛的腿的长度为3英寸。 5. The shipwrecks span nearly a century. 这些船只残骸已有近百年历史。', '过去式: spanned 过去分词: spanned 现在分词: spanning 第三人称单数: spans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conservation', '[ˌkɑːnsər\'veɪʃn]', 'n.保存；保护；守恒；节约', '1. If I may refer back to the problem we discussed, I think we shall stress on the conservation of our natural resource. 请允许我重提我们刚才讨论过的问题，我想我们应该强调保存我们的自然资源。 2. Conservation methods will also help meet their energy needs. 能量保存方法也会有利于满足其能源需求。 3. Most people have come to accept the need for conservation of natural resources. 现在大多数人已认识到保护自然资源的必要。 4. Our community is a leader in the conservation of wildlife. 我们社区在野生动物保护方面走在前头。', '形容词: conservational');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ceremonial', '[ˌserɪ\'moʊniəl]', 'n.仪式 adj.仪式的', '1. The visit was conducted with all due ceremonial. 访问按照一切应有的礼仪进行。 2. They divested the king of his ceremonial robes. 他们脱去国王的礼袍。 3. Ceremonial visits between companies is necessary. 公司之间礼节性的拜访还是需要的。 4. Some people did not like this ceremonial style. 有些人不喜欢这种拘于仪式的作风。', '副词: ceremonially 名词: ceremonialism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('turbulent', '[\'tɜːrbjələnt]', 'adj.狂暴的；骚动的；动荡的；汹涌的', '1. He was born in that turbulent period of history. 他出生在那个动荡的历史时期。 2. In the turbulent war age, he guides the elf to know the death aright. 在动荡的战争年代，他导引精灵们正确认识死亡。 3. The oarsman was feathering through the turbulent waves. 划桨者正平掠过汹涌的波浪。 4. The Rhosili is a turbulent, swift-flowing river, full of dangerous rapids and currents. 罗西里是一条汹涌的迅速滚滚的河，充满着危险的险滩和湍流。', '副词: turbulently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prod', '[prɑːd]', 'n.刺针；刺棒；戳；刺激；激励 v.戳；刺；刺激', '1. She gave the man a prod with her umbrella. 她用伞捅了那男子一下。 2. He\'s forgetful, so I\'ll give his memory a prod. 他很健忘,所以我要提醒他一下。 3. You\'ll have to give him a prod or he\'ll never get it finished. 你要给他一些激励，否则他永远都完不成。 4. He prodded at the pig with his walking-stick. 他用手杖推那口猪。', '名词: prodder 过去式: prodded 过去分词: prodded 现在分词: prodding 第三人称单数: prods');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fidelity', '[fɪ\'deləti]', 'n.忠实；忠诚；准确性；保真度', '1. Waley was much more interested in readability than fidelity. 韦利在翻译该书时更加关注译文的可读性，而非忠实程度。 2. His fidelity and industry brought him speedy promotion. 他的忠于职守和勤于工作使他得到迅速晋级。 3. She praised his servant for his fidelity. 她称赞他仆人的忠诚。 4. They betokened their fidelity to the leader with a vow. 他们以宣誓来表示他们对领袖的忠诚。', '名词复数: fidelities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dolphin', '[\'dɑːlfɪn]', 'n.海豚', '1. The dolphin is an intelligent animal. 海豚是聪明的动物。 2. We like to see the performance of dolphins. 我们喜欢看海豚的表演。 3. The dolphin balanced the ball on its nose. 海豚用鼻子顶着球，使其保持平衡。 4. They have taught a new trick to the dolphin. 他们教给了海豚一种新的把戏。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spew', '[spjuː]', 'v.喷出；涌出；呕吐；吐出 n.呕吐物；喷出物', '1. The volcano spewed molten lava. 火山喷出了熔岩。 2. Water spewed out of the hole. 水从孔中射出。 3. She spewed up the entire meal. 她把吃的饭全吐出来了。', '名词: spewer 过去式: spewed 过去分词: spewed 现在分词: spewing 第三人称单数: spews');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prosperous', '[\'prɑːspərəs]', 'adj.繁荣的；兴旺的', '1. At no time has the country been more prosperous than at present. 我国任何时候都没有现在这样繁荣。 2. There are some areas of poverty, but the country as a whole is fairly prosperous. 这个国家有些地区比较贫困, 但总的来说是相当富裕的。 3. The city at one time must have been prosperous, for It enjoyed a high level of civilization. 这座古城在一个时期准是很繁荣的，因为它曾享有高度文明。 4. His business is prosperous. 他的事业兴旺发达。', '副词: prosperously 名词: prosperousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fallible', '[\'fæləbl]', 'adj.易犯错误的；可能不正确的', '1. Human beings are only fallible. 人类本身易犯错误 2. Attention, please, this is the most fallible course. 这是比较容易出问题的环节。 3. Everybody is fallible. 人人都难免有错。 4. Memory is selective and fallible. 记忆有选择性而且会出错。', '副词: fallibly 名词: fallibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fanaticism', '[fə\'nætɪsɪzəm]', 'n.狂热；盲从', '1. Your fanaticism followed the girl is wrong. 你对那个女孩的狂热是错误的。 2. Zeal without knowledge is fanaticism. 无知的热情就是盲目的狂热。 3. To crush fanaticism and to venerate the infinite, such is the law. 压制热狂，崇敬无极，这才是正道。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ironically', '[aɪ\'rɒnɪkli]', 'adv.讽刺地；说反话地', '1. Ironically, he is the son of a policeman. 讽刺地是，他是一个警察的儿子。 2. Ironically, he was in fact opposed to capital punishment and hoped this would lead eventually to abolition. 讽刺地，他实际上是反对死刑的，希望会被废除。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('superstition', '[ˌsuːpər\'stɪʃn]', 'n.迷信；没有根据的理论', '1. It\'s a common superstition that black cats are unlucky. 认为黑猫不吉利，这是一种普遍的迷信思想。 2. He holds that ignorance leads to superstition. 他认为无知会导致迷信。 3. That superstition was prevalent among them. 那种迷信在他们之间广为流传。 4. The superstition still lingers on among them. 那种迷信仍然残留在他们的脑海中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inaugurate', '[ɪ\'nɔːɡjəreɪt]', 'v.举行就职典礼；举行仪式；开始；开创', '1. Mr. Clinton was inaugurated as the President of the U.S.A. 克林顿就职美国总统。 2. The city library was inaugurated by the mayor. 市长主持了市图书馆的落成仪式。 3. Watt inaugurated the age of steam. 瓦特开创了蒸汽时代。', '名词: inaugurator 过去式: inaugurated 过去分词: inaugurated 现在分词: inaugurating 第三人称单数: inaugurates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('conceive', '[kən\'siːv]', 'v.设想；想出；怀孕', '1. I cannot conceive of him as a genius. 我不能设想他会是一个天才。 2. I cannot conceive that he would wish to harm us. 我不能想像他会伤害我们。 3. I can not conceive of anything funnier than that . 我想不出有比那更有趣的东西。 4. She was told she couldn\'t conceive. 她得知自己不能怀孕。', '形容词: conceivable 副词: conceivably 名词: conceivability 过去式: conceived 过去分词: conceived 现在分词: conceiving 第三人称单数: conceives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meteorology', '[ˌmiːtiə\'rɑːlədʒi]', 'n.气象学；气象状态', '1. When it comes to meteorology,I\'m just a layman. 谈到气象学，我只是个门外汉。', '形容词: meteorological 副词: meteorologically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('turtle', '[\'tɜːrtl]', 'n.高翻领；【动】龟，海龟 v.倾覆，翻身；捕龟', '1. The turtle doesn\'t run so quickly as the hare. 乌龟没有兔子跑得那么快。 2. As the turtle swims across the oceanarium, the first porpoise swoops down from above and butts his shell with his belly. 当海龟游过水族馆时，第一只海豚从上方猛扑下去，并用腹部撞击龟壳。 3. An old shellfish or turtle with a growth of algae on its back. 绿毛龟一种背上有绿色水藻的老的水生贝壳类动物或海龟 4. They caught a large turtle on the shore. 他们在海滩上捉到一只大海龟。', '名词: turtler 过去式: turtled 过去分词: turtled 现在分词: turtling 第三人称单数: turtles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commodity', '[kə\'mɑːdəti]', 'n.商品；日用品；有价值之物', '1. Coal is becoming a rare commodity. 煤正在成为一种稀缺商品。 2. In spite of the depression, the price of commodity is still high 尽管有些萧条,但商品的价格仍然很高。 3. The country is heavily dependent on its exports of agricultural commodities. 这个国家很大程度上依靠农产品的出口。 4. Time is our most valuable commodity. 时间是最有价值之物。', '名词复数: commodities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entry', '[\'entri]', 'n.进入；进入权；入口；条目', '1. He pretended not to observe our entry. 他装作没有看见我们进来。 2. The people without a ticket are denied entry. 没有票的人不许入内。 3. He has applied for an entry visa. 他已申请入境签证。 4. You can leave your umbrella in the entry. 雨伞可放在入口处。', '名词复数: entries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shed', '[ʃed]', 'vt.除掉；使脱落；使流出；使清晰 n.小屋；车棚', '1. This method can help students shed inhibitions. 这一方法能帮助学生去除顾虑。 2. Most trees shed their leaves in autumn. 大多数树在秋天落叶。 3. It\'s too late to change your mind now and there is no point in shedding tears. 你现在改变主意已经太迟了,而且为此伤心落泪是毫无用处的。 4. Can you shed any light on the situation? 你能说明一下这个情形吗？ 5. The snow has banked up against the shed. 雪在小屋旁聚积起来。', '过去式: shed 过去分词: shed 现在分词: shedding 第三人称单数: sheds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('disarrange', '[ˌdɪsə\'reɪndʒ]', 'vt.扰乱；弄乱', '1. Nothing swaggered with a raucous noise to disarrange the perfect harmony. 没有任何东西以粗哑刺耳的噪音扰乱这完美的和谐。', '名词: disarrangement 过去式: disarranged 过去分词: disarranged 现在分词: disarranging 第三人称单数: disarranges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assess', '[ə\'ses]', 'v.评定；评估；估算', '1. He can quickly assess a person\'s character. 他能很快地评定出某人的品质。 2. How do you assess your students? 你如何评估学生们？ 3. We will assess the damages caused by the flood. 我们将对洪灾造成的损失进行评估。 4. She looked at the house and assessed its market value. 她看了看房子并估算了其市场价值。', '形容词: assessable 过去式: assessed 过去分词: assessed 现在分词: assessing 第三人称单数: assesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solitary', '[\'sɑːləteri]', 'adj.孤独的；独立的；单个的；唯一的；荒凉的 n.隐士；单独禁闭', '1. His childhood was repressed and solitary. 他的童年是压抑而孤独的。 2. The trapper leads a solitary life in the mountains. 那个设陷阱捕猎的人孤独地生活在山里。 3. Solitary as their lives were, is there no one person who would serve my purpose? 尽管他们过的是遗世独立的生活，难道就没有一个能够对我的计划有帮助的人吗? 4. A solitary rider was seen in the distance. 远处有个孤零零的骑马的人。', '副词: solitarily 名词: solitariness 名词复数: solitaries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assimilate', '[ə\'sɪməleɪt]', 'v.使同化；吸收', '1. The USA has assimilated people from many different countries. 美国已经同化了许多来自不同国家的人。 2. Europeans and Jews do not readily assimilate. 欧洲人和犹太人不易同化。 3. Immigrants often want to assimilate quickly. 移民经常想迅速同化。 4. Some foods are assimilated more easily than others. 有些食物比另一些食物容易吸收。', '名词: assimilator 过去式: assimilated 过去分词: assimilated 现在分词: assimilating 第三人称单数: assimilates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solemn', '[\'sɑːləm]', 'adj.庄严的；严肃的；隆重的', '1. The ceremony proceeded in a solemn atmosphere. 仪式在庄严的气氛中进行。 2. They watched the solemn ceremony. 他们观看那庄严的仪式。 3. He looked at her with a solemn expression. 他表情严肃地望着她。 4. Her solemn face told them that the news was bad. 她严肃的表情告诉他们那是坏消息。', '副词: solemnly 名词: solemnness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pious', '[\'paɪəs]', 'adj.虔诚的；伪善的；不太可能实现的', '1. He is a pious Christian. 他是一名虔诚的基督教徒。 2. He is a pious person to his belief. 他是一个对其信仰虔诚的人。 3. Honest doubt is better than in a pious fraud. 诚实的怀疑胜过伪善的信任。 4. Congress did no more than set out some pious hopes. 国会除了提出一些不可能实现的希望之外别无所为。', '副词: piously 名词: piousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nominate', '[\'nɑːmɪneɪt]', 'vt.提名；指派；登记赛马参加比赛', '1. I nominate Bill for the club president. 我提名比尔为俱乐部主席候选人。 2. Only students may nominate someone for the award. 只有学生才可以提名一些教师去拿这个奖项。 3. The board nominated him as the new director. 董事会指定他为新董事。', '名词: nominator 过去式: nominated 过去分词: nominated 现在分词: nominating 第三人称单数: nominates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('era', '[\'ɪrə]', 'n.纪元；时代；年代', '1. Concorde inaugurated new era in aeroplane travel. 协和式飞机开创了空中旅行的新纪元。 2. His death marked the end of an era. 他的死标志著一个时代的结束。 3. We are living in the computer era. 我们正生活在计算机时代。 4. It\'s an era of the miniskirt in the seventies. 七十年代是超短裙时代。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('languid', '[\'læŋɡwɪd]', 'adj.不活泼的；无精打采的；迟缓的', '1. The incredible summer heat and humidity made us all feel languid. 夏天超乎想像的热气与湿度让大家都觉得无精打采。 2. I was angry with his languid movements. 我被他那懒洋洋的动作激怒了。 3. He speaks with a languid drawl. 他慢吞吞拉着长调说话。', '副词: languidly 名词: languidness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shore', '[ʃɔːr]', 'n.岸；滨', '1. The breakers came tumbling onto the shore. 浪涛滚滚而来拍打著岸边。 2. They anchored their ship off the shore. 他们在滨外抛锚泊船。', '过去式: shored 过去分词: shored 现在分词: shoring 第三人称单数: shores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wade', '[weɪd]', 'v.跋涉；涉水 n.跋涉', '1. I wade down a shallow pebbly stream daily. 我每天沿着一条浅的有卵石的小溪跋涉。 2. I assume that Wade discussed the quality issues with you. 我承担那跋涉与你讨论质量议题。 3. We\'ll wade the stream at its shallowest point. 我们将在小河最浅的地方涉水过去。 4. A child can wade across them without a parent\'s cautions. 无须父母的告诫，孩子们就可以涉水而过。 5. I wade down a shallow pebbly stream daily. 我每天沿着一条浅的有卵石的小溪跋涉。', '过去式: waded 过去分词: waded 现在分词: wading 第三人称单数: wades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('captive', '[\'kæptɪv]', 'n.俘虏；迷恋者 adj.被俘的；被迷住的', '1. The captive was whooped and jeered. 俘虏被叱责讥笑。 2. We were held captive for three months. 我们当了三个月俘虏。 3. If a hero is of any importance, Homer also mentions the captive girl with whom he shares his tent and his bed. 荷马的史诗每提到一个重要的英雄，都要讲到同他共享帐篷和枕席的被俘的姑娘。 4. With full knowledge that the experiments were conducted on captive humans, the U.S. recruited the doctors to work for them. 在充分了解到在被俘的人身上进行的实验，美国招募了这批医生为他们工作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('realize', '[\'riːəlaɪz]', 'vt.实现；了解；意识到；变卖', '1. My wishes have been realized. 我的愿望实现了。 2. Now I will step forward to realize this wish. 现在,我想传递并实现这个愿望。 3. Master teaches us this so that we will pursue spiritual practice and realize the permanence of our God nature. 师父教导我们这个道理,好让我们努力修行以了解佛性才是永恒。 4. We figure that when you see us all, and realize the way we feel, you\'ll maybe change your minds. 估计你们见到我们这些人,了解到我们的心情之后,说不定会回心转意吧。', '形容词: realizable 名词: realizer 过去式: realized 过去分词: realized 现在分词: realizing 第三人称单数: realizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('kindle', '[\'kɪndl]', 'v.燃烧；使 ... 着火；激起；发亮', '1. The wood was wet and wouldn\'t kindle easily. 这木柴太湿，不易燃烧。 2. The sparks kindled the dry grass. 有些火星把干草给引着了。 3. The speaker tried to kindle the crowd\'s interest with a lively speech. 演讲者试图以生动活泼的讲话来激起听众的兴趣。 4. Her eyes kindled with excitement. 她的眼睛里闪耀出激动的神色。', '名词: kindler 过去式: kindled 过去分词: kindled 现在分词: kindling 第三人称单数: kindles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fasten', '[\'fæsn]', 'vt.拴紧；使固定；系；强加于 vi.固定；系紧；抓紧', '1. Do not fasten all the windows up while you sleep. 睡觉时不要将所有的窗户都关紧。 2. For your own safety,please fasten your seat belts. 安全起见，请系紧安全带。 3. I fastened the pages together with a paperclip. 我用一个纸夹把那几页纸夹在一起。 4. The little boy has learnt to fasten shoelaces. 这小男孩已学会系鞋带了。 5. What can I use to fasten on this clip? 我用什么才能将这个夹子固定好?', '名词: fastener 过去式: fastened 过去分词: fastened 现在分词: fastening 第三人称单数: fastens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ivory', '[\'aɪvəri]', 'n.象牙；乳白色', '1. The men trafficked with the natives for ivory. 这些人与土着居民做买卖以换取象牙。 2. The professor lived in an ivory tower. 这个教授生活在象牙塔中。 3. His nails resemble the ivory keys of the spinet. 他的指甲象白色的琴键一样。', '名词复数: ivories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('receptor', '[rɪ\'septər]', 'n.感受器；受体；接受器；受话器', '1. The team estimates that the kakapo has 667 functional olfactory receptor genes. 研究小组估计新西兰鹦鹉有667个起作用的嗅觉感受器基因。 2. Placebo effect tied to brain receptor activity. 安慰剂的效果与大脑内受体活动度有关。 3. Receptor and ligand are transported elsewhere. 受体和配基在别处被传递。 4. The gene affects the androgen receptor, a protein that helps activate male hormones. 这种基因影响男性荷尔蒙接受器，这是一种帮助激活男性荷尔蒙的蛋白质。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flint', '[flɪnt]', 'n.打火石；极硬的东西', '1. It is possible to strike fire from flint. 火石可以打火。 2. This layer of rock contains a lot of flint. 这一岩层中有大量燧石。 3. He has a heart of flint. 他有一副铁石心肠。 4. She gave him a look as hard as flint. 她冷酷地瞪他一眼。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('redundant', '[rɪ\'dʌndənt]', 'adj.多余的，过多的；累赘的，冗长的；解雇的；重复的，千篇一律的', '1. Skill has been made redundant by machine. 由于使用机器，手艺已变得多余。 2. This word is redundant, it can be left out. 这个字是多余的, 可以去掉。 3. There are too many redundant words in this book. 这本书里多余的词太多。', '副词: redundantly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jurisdiction', '[ˌdʒʊrɪs\'dɪkʃn]', 'n.管辖权；司法权；审判权；控制权', '1. This affair is within his jurisdiction. 这件事情在他的管辖权限之内。 2. The village you speak of does not fall under my jurisdiction. 你所说的这个村庄不在我的管辖范围内。 3. That case is under the jurisdiction of this court. 那宗案件属本法庭受理范围。 4. The court has no jurisdiction over foreign diplomats living in this country. 法院对居住在本国的外交官无裁判权。', '形容词: jurisdictional 副词: jurisdictionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('attract', '[ə\'trækt]', 'v.吸引；引来', '1. The flower show attracted large crowds this year. 今年的花展吸引了大批观众。 2. She gave a quiet cough to attract my attention. 她轻轻地咳了一声好引起我注意。 3. His comments were bound to attract criticism. 他的评论必然会招致批评。', '形容词: attractable 名词: attracter 过去式: attracted 过去分词: attracted 现在分词: attracting 第三人称单数: attracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('humorous', '[\'hjuːmərəs]', 'adj.幽默的；诙谐的', '1. I have plenty of humorous tales. 我有许多幽默的故事。 2. Indeed he has a solemn face, but he is very humorous at heart. 他的确有一副严肃的脸孔，但内心却是很富幽默感。 3. She writes humorous songs when she is in the right vein. 她在心情不好的时候写诙谐的歌曲。 4. It tells a romantic and humorous love. 它讲述了一个浪漫而诙谐的爱情故事。', '副词: humorously 名词: humorousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('geometry', '[dʒi\'ɑːmətri]', 'n.几何；几何学', '1. I feel that geometry is a difficult subject. 我认为几何是一门难学的课程。 2. Today we have a lesson in geometry. 今天，我们有一节几何课。 3. Leon didn\'t finish his geometry homework because his mind kept jumping the track to think about the new girl in class. 利昂没完成几何作业，因为他思想总在开小差，想着班上新来的女生。 4. The boy puzzled his way through geometry. 那男孩煞费苦心地钻研几何学。', '名词: geometrician 名词复数: geometries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intent', '[ɪn\'tent]', 'adj.热切的；专心的；决心的 n.意图；目的；意向；含义', '1. He\'s intent on going to Australia. 他热切希望到澳大利亚去。 2. Her intent look showed how much she had missed her sister. 她的专心的目光说明她是多么想念她的姐姐。 3. He\'s intent on moneymaking. 他一心一意地赚钱。 4. She is intent on getting the job done quickly. 她决心尽快把这件事情做好。 5. No one could spy out the intent and meaning of it. 没有人能查出它的意图和意义。', '副词: intently 名词: intentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slim', '[slɪm]', 'adj.苗条的；微小的；细长的 v.减肥；缩减', '1. I wish I was as slim as you. 但愿我能像你一样苗条 2. I remember her (ie picture her in my mind) as a slim young girl. 我想起她那时还是个苗条的少女。 3. He showed much enthusiasm for our plan.1329286376:435972 滚开 4. I have a slim gold watch. 我有一块细长的金表。 5. She is trying to slim by jogging. 她正用跑步法来减肥。', '副词: slimly 比较级: slimmer 最高级: slimmest 名词: slimmer 过去式: slimmed 过去分词: slimmed 现在分词: slimming 第三人称单数: slims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('democracy', '[dɪ\'mɑːkrəsi]', 'n.民主国家；民主；民主制', '1. Greece must have a system if it is to become a self supporting and self respecting democracy. 要想成为一个自立、自尊的民主国家，希腊必须有一个健全的体制。 2. The election demonstrates democracy in action. 这次选举是以实际行动体现了民主。 3. Democracy is a bulwark of freedom. 民主是自由的保障。 4. The military government promised to restore democracy within one year. 军人政府答应在一年内重新建立民主体制。', '名词复数: democracies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('edify', '[\'edɪfaɪ]', 'vt. <古>建立； 训导； 教导； 启发； 薰陶', '1. A sermon, especially one intended to edify a congregation on a practical matter and not intended to be a theological discourse. 布道一次讲道，尤其是旨在于实际问题上启发会众，而不在于成为神学讲演 2. This is an edifying book. 这是一本陶冶情操的书。 3. Travel is an edifying experience, especially for young people. 旅游可以使人增长见闻，尤其对年轻人。', '名词: edifier 过去式: edified 过去分词: edified 现在分词: edifying 第三人称单数: edifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('recommend', '[ˌrekə\'mend]', 'vt.推荐；建议；劝告；使受欢迎；使可取', '1. Can you recommend me some new books on this subject? 你能推荐一些有关这个学科的新书给我吗? 2. I should recommend it as a useful reference book. 我愿意推荐它作为一本有用的参考书。 3. I recommend you to buy this dictionary and that tape. 我建议你买这本字典和那盒磁带。 4. I recommend that you inquire about the job. 我建议你打听一下这项工作。', '形容词: recommendable 名词: recommender 过去式: recommended 过去分词: recommended 现在分词: recommending 第三人称单数: recommends');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('defective', '[dɪ\'fektɪv]', 'adj.有缺陷的；[语]不完全变化的 n.有缺陷的人', '1. He is mentally defective. 他智力不健全。 2. She has a defective utterance. 她发音有缺陷。 3. Please return defective merchandise in three days. 请于三日内退还缺陷的商品。 4. \"Ought\" is a defective verb. \"ought\"是变化不完全的动词。 5. We decided to make all the defective sheet up. 我们决定全部重印有缺陷的页码。', '副词: defectively 名词: defectiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('collide', '[kə\'laɪd]', 'vi.碰撞；互撞；砥触', '1. The bus and the van collided. 公共汽车与客货车相撞。 2. The ships collided in the fog. 轮船在雾中相撞。 3. As the bus turned the corner, it collided with a van. 公共汽车转过拐角时与客货车相撞。 4. But during the collision, one galaxy can rip the other apart gravitationally, and dust and gas common to both galaxies does collide. 当星系互撞期间，星系可能因重力拉扯另外一个星系，尘埃与云气也会因此而合并。', '过去式: collided 过去分词: collided 现在分词: colliding 第三人称单数: collides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impertinent', '[ɪm\'pɜːrtnənt]', 'adj.鲁莽的；无礼的；粗鲁的；离题的', '1. The impertinent remarks teed the speaker off. 这鲁莽的评论激怒了演讲者。 2. I\'ve had enough of your impertinent words. 你说话太不礼貌了，我已受够了。 3. The impertinent boy put his tongue out at me. 那个无礼的男孩子对我吐舌头。 4. This is a point impertinent to the argument. 这是一个离题太远的论点。', '副词: impertinently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reciprocal', '[rɪ\'sɪprəkl]', 'adj.互惠的；相互的；互补的 n.相互；互惠；[数]倒数', '1. Thus there is an important reciprocal relationship between honesty and trust. 基于此,诚实与信任成为重要的互惠关系。 2. It is mutually Beneficial and reciprocal to do this deal with the Japanese. 与日本人做这笔生意，互利互惠。 3. They show reciprocal affection to each other. 他们表达了彼此之间的爱慕。 4. Although I gave him many presents, I had no reciprocal gifts from him. 虽然我给他很多礼物, 但我没有收到过他给我的礼物。 5. I trust the reciprocal nature of our love. 我相信爱情是相互的。', '副词: reciprocally 名词: reciprocality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('confident', '[\'kɒnfədənt]', 'adj.自信的；有信心的；有把握的', '1. For my own part, being nice about appearance keeps me confident. 就我而论，注重仪表使我自信。 2. I\'m confident in the path I have chosen. 我对我自己选择的道路有绝对的自信。 3. Your encouragement made me more confident of my future. 你的鼓励使我对我的未来更加有信心。 4. One has to be confident in himself. 一个人一定要对自己有信心。', '副词: confidently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('marvel', '[\'mɑːrvl]', 'n.奇异的事物；令人吃惊的人 v.惊异于；惊异', '1. Your room is a marvel of neatness and order. 你的房间整洁得出奇。 2. The operation was a marvel of medical skill. 这个手术是医术的一个非凡范例。 3. It was a real marvel that the baby was unhurt when he fell from the fifth floor. 那婴儿从五楼摔下来竟没受伤真是一个奇迹。 4. You\'re a marvel; how can you work so hard at your age. 您是一位奇才;象您这么大年纪的人怎么会这么拼命干呢。 5. I marvel at the felicity of his style. 我惊叹他的精巧的文体。', '过去式: marveled/marvelled 过去分词: marveled/marvelled 现在分词: marveling/marvelling 第三人称单数: marvels/marvels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('credential', '[krə\'denʃl]', 'n.国书；凭据；印信 vt.提供证明书 adj.信任的', '1. Is the name of the credential to remove from the server. 要从服务器中删除的凭据的名称。 2. The passwords that are used to protect the master keys are stored in the credential store. 用于保护主密钥的密码存储在凭据存储区中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barren', '[\'bærən]', 'adj.贫瘠的；无效的；不育的 n.荒地', '1. No one could raise crops on this barren land. 没人能够在这么贫瘠的土地上种庄稼。 2. Life is a barren field frozen with snow. 生命就像是被雪覆盖的荒芜土地。 3. We shall turn this piece of barren land into wheat fields. 我们要把这块不毛之地变为麦田。 4. He was engaged in a barren argument with Paul. 他在同保罗作无用的争论。', '副词: barrenly 名词: barrenness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('glow', '[ɡloʊ]', 'n.光辉；热情；赤热 vi.发红光；红光焕发', '1. There is a glow of health in his face. 他的脸容光焕发。 2. There midnight\'s all a glimmer and noon (is) a purple glow. 那儿午夜浮光微摇，中午紫光争耀。 3. The sunset glow is very beautiful. 太阳的余辉非常美丽。 4. His face took on an affectionate glow. 他的脸上洋溢着热情的红光。 5. All fireflies glow with about the same brightness. 所有的萤火虫闪耀着差不多相同的光亮。', '过去式: glowed 过去分词: glowed 现在分词: glowing 第三人称单数: glows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dissemble', '[dɪ\'sembl]', 'v.掩饰；假装', '1. She tried to dissemble her anger with a smile on her face. 她试图用她脸上的微笑来掩饰她的愤怒。 2. I tried to dissemble an interest I didn\'t feel. 我设法假装感兴趣。', '副词: dissemblingly 名词: dissemblance 过去式: dissembled 过去分词: dissembled 现在分词: dissembling 第三人称单数: dissembles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('haunt', '[hɔːnt]', 'n.常到的地方 vt.缠住；常到；出没(像鬼魂一样) vi.徘徊；出没(像鬼魂一样)', '1. The college library is a favorite haunt. 大学图书馆是人们喜欢的地方。 2. His youthful escapades came back to haunt him. 年轻时的胡作非为时常令他感到苦恼。 3. The memory in later times returned to haunt him. 那回忆后来经常浮现在他脑海。 4. Her wishful face haunt my dream like the rai at ight. 她的热切的脸，如夜雨似的，搅扰着我的梦魂。 5. The area was a haunt of criminals. 这个地区是罪犯经常出没的地方。', '名词: haunter 过去式: haunted 过去分词: haunted 现在分词: haunting 第三人称单数: haunts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('justice', '[\'dʒʌstɪs]', 'n.公平；公正；正义；司法；法官；法律制裁', '1. I won\'t dispute the justice of his remarks. 我不怀疑他的话是公平合理的。 2. Marriage is, first of all, a contract which must be governed by justice. 婚姻首先是一种契约，它必须以公正为制约。 3. Justice triumphs in the end. 正义终将得胜。 4. British justice works on the premise that an accused person is innocent until he\'s proved guilty. 英国司法运作的前提是被告在被证明有罪之前是清白的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('desirable', '[dɪ\'zaɪərəbl]', 'adj.令人满意的；性感的；有吸引力的；值得的；令人向往的 n.有吸引力的人或物', '1. It is desirable that we (should) provide for the poor at Christmas. 在圣诞节施舍穷人是可喜的事。 2. It is desirable that atomic energy should be used for peaceful purpose. 原子能应该为了和平的目的而使用，这是合乎情理的。 3. You will also make some desirable acquaintances. 你也可以结识几个合意的朋友。 4. He found her intensely desirable. 他觉得她极其性感。 5. The girl is a desirable. 这个女孩是个有吸引力的人。', '副词: desirably 名词: desirability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bestow', '[bɪ\'stoʊ]', 'v.授予；给予；<古>使用；<古>放置', '1. The trophy was bestowed upon the winner. 奖品授给了优胜者。 2. He wished to bestow great honors upon the hero. 他希望将那些伟大的荣誉授予这位英雄。 3. The surgeon bestowed eyesight on my blind son. 外科医生给了我的盲人儿子视力。 4. Bestow less time on daydreaming. 少花时间胡思乱想吧。', '形容词: bestowable 名词: bestowal 过去式: bestowed 过去分词: bestowed 现在分词: bestowing 第三人称单数: bestows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tension', '[\'tenʃn]', 'n.紧张；拉力；张力；紧张状态；[电]电压 vt.使拉紧；使绷紧', '1. The tension is building up. 形势逐步紧张起来。 2. The tension soon transmitted itself to all the members of the crowd. 这种紧张情绪很快感染了人群中所有的人。 3. A positive-stress component means tension. 正应力分量表示拉力。 4. If a wire is held under tension, it gets slightly longer. 电线在拉力状态下会变得略微长点。', '形容词: tensional 过去式: tensioned 过去分词: tensioned 现在分词: tensioning 第三人称单数: tensions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flare', '[fler]', 'n.闪光；闪光信号；[天]耀斑；(衣裙等)张开 v.闪光；闪耀；爆发；张开', '1. The flare of the match lit up his face. 火柴的光照亮了他的脸。 2. He stood ready to fire a warning flare. 他站着准备发出警告信号。 3. One possibility is that the blast was like an ultra-powerful solar flare. 一种可能的原因是这种爆炸很像有超级能量的太阳耀斑。 4. These flows occurred after violently unstable magnetic reconnection events above the Sun produced the flare. 这些在太阳表面上空剧烈而又不稳定的磁重联事件会产生耀斑。 5. A gust of wind made the candles flare. 一阵风吹得烛光摇曳。', '过去式: flared 过去分词: flared 现在分词: flaring 第三人称单数: flares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('practical', '[\'præktɪkl]', 'adj.明智的；实际的；实用的；事实上的 n.实践考试', '1. A practical person does not spend his money and time foolishly. 一个有头脑的人是不胡乱花钱和虚度光阴的。 2. It\'s an interesting idea, but there are many practical difficulties. 这是一个很有意思的想法,然而却存在着许多实际困难。 3. Most importantly, we should develop our own practical ability. 最重要的是,我们应该提高自身的实践能力。 4. Your invention is not practical. 你的发明不实用。 5. His practical at the hospital went well enough. 他在医院的实习进行得相当好。', '名词: practicality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('entity', '[\'entəti]', 'n.实体；存在；本质', '1. A corporation is treated by the law as an entity. 法人在法律上被视为一个实体。 2. It describes the change in an entity\'s state. 它描述了一个实体的状态变化。', '名词复数: entities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maturity', '[mə\'tʃʊrəti]', 'n.成熟；(支票等的)到期', '1. My plan has gradually come to maturity. 我的计划逐渐成熟。 2. His performance was full of maturity and poise. 他的表现成熟而稳健。 3. It takes roughly forty years for the trees to reach maturity. 这些树木要花近四十年才能进入成熟期。 4. The interest on term deposit is only due at maturity. 定期存款利息必须到期支付。', '名词复数: maturities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solicit', '[sə\'lɪsɪt]', 'vt.恳求；征求；勾引 vi.(妓女)拉客', '1. We solicit your close cooperation with us in this matter. 我们恳求您对于此一事件能给予协助和合作。 2. We should often solicit opinions from the masses . 我们应该经常征求群众意见。 3. They were planning to solicit funds from a number of organizations. 他们正计划向一些机构募集资金。 4. To solicit a judge means to offer him bribes. 引诱法官就是给予贿胳。 5. She was fined for soliciting. 她因拉客而被罚款。', '名词: solicitation 过去式: solicited 过去分词: solicited 现在分词: soliciting 第三人称单数: solicits');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decree', '[dɪ\'kriː]', 'n.法令；判决 v.颁布；裁定；注定', '1. This decree obliges unions to delay strikes . 这项法令使协会不得不推迟罢工。 2. The decree imposed strict censorship of the media. 这个法令强制实行严格的媒体审查制度。 3. The final decree dissolved their marriage. 最后的判决解除了他们的婚姻关系。 4. This decree has the force of law behind it. 这一裁决有法律的力量作后盾。 5. The dictator decreed that his birthday would be a public holiday. 该独裁者发布命令，将其生日定为公众假期。', '形容词: decreeable 名词: decreer 过去式: decreed 过去分词: decreed 现在分词: decreeing 第三人称单数: decrees');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('animation', '[ˌænɪ\'meɪʃn]', 'n.活泼；生气；兴奋；动画片；动画片制作', '1. They talked of their holiday plans with great animation. 他们非常起劲地谈着度假计划。 2. He was full of colour and animation. 他充满魅力,生机勃勃。 3. We felt an animation about the ambitious plan. 我们对此宏伟规划感到兴奋。 4. The animation is awesome and gets better and better every year. 动画片尤其精采，而且一年比一年好看。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annual', '[\'ænjuəl]', 'adj.每年的；年度的；一年生的 n.年刊；一年生植物', '1. The firm has an annual turnover of $75 million. 这家公司的年营业额为7500万美元。 2. Now, again, his annual trip to Paris begins. 现在,他一年一度的巴黎之行又开始了。 3. The kind of plant is a hardy annual. 这种植物是耐寒的一年生植物。 4. Annual or perennial herbs, or tall woody bamboos. 一年生或多年生草本，或高的木质的竹子。 5. His essay is copied from a college annual. 他的论文是从一本大学年刊上抄下来的。', '副词: annually');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cone', '[koʊn]', 'n.圆锥体；锥形物；球果 vt.变成锥形', '1. Saw-dust has piled up in a great cone. 锯屑堆积如山。 2. The police have sectioned off the road with traffic cone. 警察用锥形路标把路面分隔开来。 3. The little boy likes to eat the ice-cream cone. 小男孩喜欢吃冰淇淋蛋卷。 4. The staminate cone of pine is male rather than female. 松树雄球果是雄性而非雌性。 5. They coned off a section of motorway during repairs. 他们用锥形标志隔开维修中的一段高速公路。', '过去式: coned 过去分词: coned 现在分词: coning 第三人称单数: cones');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('implication', '[ˌɪmplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.牵连；含意；暗示；卷入', '1. His implication in the crime was obvious to all. 大家都清楚他和这一罪行有牵连。 2. The trial resulted in the implication of several major figures in the organization. 审讯结果表明这个组织中几个主要人物都牵连在案。 3. He has not actually realized the full implication. 他还没有真正认识到全部含意。 4. The new report has far-reaching implications for the future of broadcasting. 这一新报告对广播业的前途有些意味深长的暗示。', '形容词: implicative 副词: implicatively');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expansive', '[ɪk\'spænsɪv]', 'adj.易膨胀的；广阔的；滔滔不绝的；健谈的', '1. As a new material, its prospective will be more expansive in the future. 作为一种新型材料，它的发展前景十分广阔。 2. Birdsong\'s answer was expansive. 伯德桑的回答是滔滔不绝的。 3. After he\'d had a few drinks, Charles became very expansive. 查尔斯喝了几杯酒，话就滔滔不绝了。 4. Today Sarah became jovial and expansive. 今天莎拉变得快活而健谈。', '副词: expansively 名词: expansiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('upset', '[ʌp\'set]', 'adj.心烦的；苦恼的；不安的；不适的 v.推翻；翻倒；颠覆；打乱；使心烦 n.混乱；推翻', '1. I\'m always upset when I don\'t get any mail. 我接不到任何邮件时总是心烦意乱。 2. There is no reason to get so upset. 完全没有理由如此心烦意乱。 3. Try not to get too upset about it. 尽量不要过于为此烦恼。 4. He was very upset that you didn\'t reply to his letters. 你没有给他回信,他很不安。 5. The generals plotted to upset the government. 将军们策划推翻政府。 6. Last-minute changes caused a great deal of upset. 出现的临时变动造成一片混乱。', '副词: upsettingly 名词: upsetter 过去式: upset 过去分词: upset 现在分词: upsetting 第三人称单数: upsets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forsake', '[fər\'seɪk]', 'v.放弃；断念；抛弃', '1. Because he chose to forsake eternal life for knowledge. 因为他为了选择知识而放弃了永生。 2. Forsake your greed, abandon your appetites of ostentation. 除去你的贪心，放弃你所炫耀的爱好。 3. Forsake learning, and you will ruin yourself. 抛弃了学问便是毁了你们自己。 4. She pleaded with her husband not to forsake her. 她恳求丈夫不要抛弃她。', '过去式: forsook 过去分词: forsaken 现在分词: forsaking 第三人称单数: forsakes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forge', '[fɔːrdʒ]', 'vt.锻造；伪造；建立 vi.伪造；做铁匠 n.锻炉；铁匠铺；锻造车间', '1. These machine parts have been forged with the finest steel. 这些机器零件得用优质的钢锻造。 2. George was forced to forge a signature. 乔治被迫伪造签名。 3. They forged their manager\'s signature on the cheque. 他们在支票上伪造了经理的签名。 4. They tried to forge an alliance. 他们试图建立同盟。 5. Some people forge official documents. 有些人伪造公文。 6. He began to heat, like iron in the forge. 他象锻炉里的铁一样热起来。', '形容词: forgeable 名词: forgeability 过去式: forged 过去分词: forged 现在分词: forging 第三人称单数: forges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('overbearing', '[ˌəʊvə\'beərɪŋ]', 'adj.傲慢的；骄傲自大的；蛮横的', '1. No one liked his overbearing manners. 没有人喜欢他那傲慢的样子。 2. His overbearing insolence angered everyone. 他的傲慢无礼激起了大家的愤怒。 3. The aging actress was very high-strung and overbearing. 这位上了年纪的女演员非常紧张,而且骄傲自大。 4. He\'s so overbearing that no one wants to work for him. 他那么蛮横,没人愿为他工作。', '副词: overbearingly 名词: overbearingness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('favorable', '[\'feɪvərəbəl]', 'adj.有利的；顺利的；良好的；赞同的', '1. The conditions are favorable for opening a new business. 各种条件有利于开办新企业。 2. He made several favorable comments about their candidate. 他对他们的候选人发表了一些有利的评论。 3. \"Our expedition made a favorable beginning. 我们远航开始的时候很顺利。 4. The book met with a favorable reception. 此书受到好评。', '副词: favorably 名词: favorableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('homestead', '[\'hoʊmsted]', 'n.家园；田产；农场 v.住在或工作在家园', '1. We must reestablish our homestead. 我们必须重建我们的家园。 2. There are many old homesteads in New England. 在新英格兰有许多古老的家宅。', '名词: homesteader 过去式: homesteaded 过去分词: homesteaded 现在分词: homesteading 第三人称单数: homesteads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('declaim', '[dɪ\'kleɪm]', 'v.高谈阔论；雄辩；大声说', '1. A preacher stood declaiming in the town centre. 传教士站在市镇中心慷慨陈词。 2. It is not a sign of humility to declaim against pride. 用慷慨激昂的言语攻击傲慢并不是谦逊的标志。 3. She wrote a book declaiming against our corrupt society. 她写了一本书抨击我们这腐败的社会。', '名词: declaimer 过去式: declaimed 过去分词: declaimed 现在分词: declaiming 第三人称单数: declaims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('leading', '[\'liːdɪŋ]', 'adj.领导的；指导的；主要的；在前的', '1. He is a leading cadre. 他是个领导干部。 2. She tried to beat up some support for the campaign she was leading. 她力求赢得人们对她所领导的运动的支持。 3. This old man is a leading authority on wheat diseases. 这位老人是小麦病虫害方面的权威。 4. The director cast her in a leading part when she was a young unknown of 16. 当她还是一个十六岁的无名少女时，导演选中她演主角。', '副词: leadingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alloy', '[\'ælɔɪ]', 'n.合金 vt.使成合金；使降低，贬损；掺以杂质 vi.有合金能力', '1. Brass is an alloy of copper and zinc. 黄铜是铜和锌的合金。 2. The alloy has excellent thermal stability. 合金有极好的温度稳定性。 3. Mercy should alloy our stern resentment. 宽容会缓和积怨。 4. Nothing occurred to alloy our happiness. 未发生任何损害我们幸福的事情。', '过去式: alloyed 过去分词: alloyed 现在分词: alloying 第三人称单数: alloys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('severe', '[sɪ\'vɪr]', 'adj.严厉的；严重的；剧烈的；严格的；严峻的', '1. The premier came under severe criticism. 这位总理遭到严厉的抨击。 2. He\'s suffering from severe mental disorder. 他患有严重的精神病。 3. A severe storm turned the small village down to ground. 一场剧烈的风暴把小村夷为平地。 4. The new product has stood a severe proof . 新产品经受了严格的考验。', '副词: severely 比较级: severer 最高级: severest 名词: severeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('yell', '[jel]', 'v.大叫 n.大喊', '1. Don\'t yell at me! 别对我大喊大叫！ 2. You don\'t have to yell; I can hear you. 你用不著喊，我听得见。 3. She yelled out at her mischievous child. 她对她淘气的孩子大喊大叫。 4. We yelled our good-byes as the bus left. 汽车离开时我们大喊再见。 5. She let out a yell and ran home. 她尖叫了一声跑回了家。', '名词: yeller 过去式: yelled 过去分词: yelled 现在分词: yelling 第三人称单数: yells');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cardiac', '[\'kɑːrdiæk]', 'adj.心脏的；心脏病的', '1. Death is caused by cardiac failure. 心脏衰竭引起死亡。 2. This increased cardiac work load! 这个增加了心脏的工作负担! 3. Jostling the patient may cause cardiac arrest. 猛烈碰撞病人可能导致心脏停止。 4. They managed to revive the injured driver with cardiac massage. 他们通过心脏按压使受伤的司机苏醒了过来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deserted', '[dɪ\'zɜːrtɪd]', 'adj.废弃的；荒芜的；被遗弃的 动词desert的过去式和过去分词.', '1. A mysterious light came from the deserted house. 废弃的房屋里亮起了神秘的灯光。 2. On another occasion, he landed in a deserted car park. 还有一次，他在一个废弃的停车场着陆。 3. They walked across a deserted land. 他们穿过一片荒芜的土地。 4. With a sinking heart, I realized that I was on a deserted island. 带著一颗深沈的心，我明白自己是在个荒芜的岛上。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vigor', '[\'vɪgə]', 'n.活力；精力', '1. He is a young lad with plenty of vigor. 他是个充满活力的小伙子。 2. They are here to drink in vigor from the youth. 他们来这里是想从年轻人身上得到活力。 3. I tackled my assignments with vigor. 凭着充沛的精力，我完成了分派给我的任务。 4. This decline in vigor with the passing of time is called ageing. 这种随着时间的流逝而精力衰退的现象我们称为衰老。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tectonics', '[tek\'tɒnɪks]', 'n.筑造学；构造学；构造地质学', '1. What does the theory of plate tectonics maintain? 这板块构造学说的理论讲些什么? 2. Plate tectonics is now almost universally accepted. 如今板块构造几乎被普遍接受。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foam', '[foʊm]', 'n.泡沫；汗 v.起泡沫；吐口沫；愤怒；沸腾', '1. The sea was flecked with foam. 大海上涌起点点泡沫。 2. Foam rubber provides good insulation. 泡沫橡胶隔绝性能良好。 3. The fire extinguisher is filled with chemical foam. 这个灭火器充满了化学泡沫。 4. When the horse had finished the race, its sides were wet with foam. 这匹马结束比赛时，它的脊背被汗水湿透了。 5. When he poured the warm beer, it foam up out of the glass. 当他倒鲜啤酒时，啤酒泛起泡沫从杯中流了出来。', '过去式: foamed 过去分词: foamed 现在分词: foaming 第三人称单数: foams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slight', '[slaɪt]', 'adj.轻微的；纤弱的；微小的 vt.轻视；忽略 n.轻蔑；怠慢', '1. He has a slight wheeze in his chest. 他呼吸时胸部发出轻微的响声。 2. Our army suffered a slight reverse. 我们的部队受到轻微的挫败。 3. The salve will heal slight burns. 这药膏能治疗轻微烧伤。 4. Her slight frame was shaken by bouts of coughing. 她纤弱的身躯因阵阵咳嗽而发颤。 5. We shouldn\'t slight anybody even if he\'s a nobody. 我们不应该轻视任何人，即使他是一个小人物。 6. I was hurt by the obvious slight. 这种明显的怠慢伤害了我的感情。', '比较级: slighter 最高级: slightest 名词: slightness 过去式: slighted 过去分词: slighted 现在分词: slighting 第三人称单数: slights');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('season', '[\'siːzn]', 'n.季节；赛季；旺季；时期 v.给 ... 调味；适应；风干', '1. Winter is the coldest season in a year. 冬季是一年中最冷的季节。 2. He will captain the basketball team next season. 他将在下个赛季担任该篮球队的队长。 3. Holiday prices are lower out of season. 在度假淡季，度假费用较低。 4. The last three years have been a good season for the company. 过去三年一直是公司的兴旺时期。 5. You can season the soup with salt and pepper. 你可以用盐和胡椒来调汤的味道。', '过去式: seasoned 过去分词: seasoned 现在分词: seasoning 第三人称单数: seasons');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apartment', '[ə\'pɑːrtmənt]', 'n.一套公寓房间', '1. I have an apartment in downtown Manhattan. 我在曼哈顿中心区有一套住房。 2. We are fascinated by the delicate interior design of the apartment. 我们被这所公寓的精致的室内装潢设计吸引。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('refund', '[\'riːfʌnd]', 'n.偿还；退款 vt.偿还；退还', '1. The residents made a claim for the refund of property tax. 居民们要求发还物业税。 2. We insisted on a refund of the full amount. 我们坚决要求全额退款。 3. Needless to say, we shall refund any expenses you may incur. 不用说，我们将会偿还你所担负的任何费用。 4. We will refund you if the purchase has any quality defect. 如果所购物品存在质量问题，我们将退款给您。', '形容词: refundable 名词: refunder 过去式: refunded 过去分词: refunded 现在分词: refunding 第三人称单数: refunds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allot', '[ə\'lɑːt]', 'vt.分配；分摊；拨给', '1. The government is ready to allot houses in that area. 政府准备在那个地区分配住房。 2. Who will she allot the easy jobs to? 她要把轻活儿分给谁? 3. You allot a certain amount of time to the markets each day. 你每天分配一定的时间研究市场。 4. Who will she allot the easy jobs to? 她要把轻活儿分给谁?', '名词: allotter 过去式: allotted 过去分词: allotted 现在分词: allotting 第三人称单数: allots');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stimulate', '[\'stɪmjuleɪt]', 'vt.刺激；激励；鼓舞 vi.起刺激作用', '1. Light stimulates plant growth. 光会刺激植物生长。 2. Alcohol stimulates the action of the heart. 酒刺激心脏的活动。 3. Praise always stimulates him to further efforts. 一表扬他就能激励他更加努力。 4. I\'m trying to stimulate him to study harder. 我试图激励他更加用功读书。', '形容词: stimulative 副词: stimulatingly 名词: stimulater 过去式: stimulated 过去分词: stimulated 现在分词: stimulating 第三人称单数: stimulates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('notify', '[\'noʊtɪfaɪ]', 'v.通知；报告；通告', '1. Please notify us of any change of address. 地址如有变动，请通知我们。 2. She notified us of the meeting. 她通知我们开会。 3. We\'ll notify her to draw up a contract. 我们将通知她起草一份合同。 4. They will notify her when to appear in court. 他们将通知她何时出庭。', '名词: notifier 过去式: notified 过去分词: notified 现在分词: notifying 第三人称单数: notifies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('absolute', '[\'æbsəluːt]', 'adj.绝对的；确实的；专制的；完全的；独立的；无限制的 n.绝对的事物', '1. There is no absolute standard for beauty. 美是没有绝对的标准的。 2. Motion is absolute, while stillness is relative. 运动是绝对的，而静止是相对的。 3. There is no absolute freedom in the world. 世上没有绝对的自由。 4. The police have absolute proof of his guilt. 警方有他犯罪的确凿证据。', '名词: absoluteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('champion', '[\'tʃæmpiən]', 'n.拥护者；冠军；优胜者；勇士 vt.拥护；保卫；为 ... 而斗争', '1. He is a champion of women\'s rights. 他是妇女权利的卫士. 2. He is the undisputed champion. 他是无可争辩的冠军。 3. He is a champion at writing familiar essays. 他是写小品文的好手。 4. Every absurdity have a champion to defend it. 任何谬论都拥有拥护它的斗士。 5. He is forced to champion unpopular causes. 他被迫去支持一些不得人心的事业。', '过去式: championed 过去分词: championed 现在分词: championing 第三人称单数: champions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('laud', '[lɔːd]', 'v.赞美 n.颂歌；赞美', '1. He was lauded for his courage. 他的勇敢受到了人们的称赞。 2. My mother lauded me yesterday. 我妈妈昨天表扬了我。 3. I will laud my enemies and they will become our friends. 我赞美敌人', '名词: lauder 过去式: lauded 过去分词: lauded 现在分词: lauding 第三人称单数: lauds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('agility', '[ə\'dʒɪləti]', 'n.敏捷；灵活；轻快', '1. The boy came upstairs with agility. 那男孩敏捷地走上楼来。 2. Each point of Agility now adds 1 Attack Power. 现在每一点敏捷将增加猫形态下的一点攻击强度。 3. The spiderman moves with feline agility. 蜘蛛人的动作像猫一们灵活。 4. It takes good agility to become a ballet dancer. 成为芭蕾舞者需要相当的灵活度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suggest', '[sə\'dʒest]', 'vt.建议；暗示；使想起；表明；要求', '1. I suggested going for a walk. 我建议去散步。 2. I suggested to him that we should tackle the problem another way. 我向他建议我们用另一种方式处理这个问题。 3. He had the effrontery to suggest that she enjoyed being unhappy. 他无耻地大胆暗示，她喜欢不幸。 4. The thought of summer suggests swimming. 想到夏天，就使人联想到游泳。', '名词: suggester 过去式: suggested 过去分词: suggested 现在分词: suggesting 第三人称单数: suggests');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('capability', '[ˌkeɪpə\'bɪləti]', 'n.能力；才能；性能；容量', '1. He had no capability to deal with the matter. 他没有能力处理那件事。 2. As a scientist, he has the capability of doing important research. 作为一个科学家,他具有从事重要科学研究的能力。 3. The engineer explained the plane\'s technical capabilities. 工程师讲解了该飞机的技术性能。 4. These calculations are beyond the capabilities of even the most advanced computers. 这些计算题甚至超出最先进的电脑运算容量。', '名词复数: capabilities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('amusement', '[ə\'mjuːzmənt]', 'n.乐趣，娱乐；消遣', '1. I find amusement in collecting stamps. 我发现了集邮的乐趣。 2. He is responsible for the amusement activity. 他负责娱乐活动。 3. His chief amusement is reading novels. 他的主要消遣是看小说。 4. I would never choose to watch cricket as an amusement. 我决不会把看板球当作消遣。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('purity', '[\'pjʊrəti]', 'n.纯净；纯洁；纯正；纯粹', '1. We must ensure the purity of drinking water. 我们必须确保饮用水的纯净。 2. Chinese people regard lotus as an emblem of purity. 中国人把莲花看作是纯洁的象征。 3. White symbolizes purity and cleanness. 白色代表纯洁和干净。 4. It\'s a soprano of great compass and of great purity. 这是一种音域宽广，高度纯正的女高音。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skip', '[skɪp]', 'v.跳过；略过；遗漏 n.跳跃；跳读；省略', '1. Lambs skipped in the field. 小羊在田野里跳跃。 2. Let\' s skip over this page and come to page 55. 咱们越过这一页，看第五十五页。 3. I read the whole book without skipping(a page). 我一页不漏地读完了整本书。 4. He gave a skip of joy as he heard the news. 得知这个消息，他高兴地跳了起来。', '形容词: skippable 过去式: skipped 过去分词: skipped 现在分词: skipping 第三人称单数: skips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('collaborator', '[kə\'læbəreɪtər]', 'n.合著者；合作者；通敌者', '1. Mary Anne Lamb was an English writer, the sister and collaborator of Charles Lamb. 玛丽·安·兰姆是一个英国作家，她是查尔斯·兰姆的姐姐和合作者。 2. We are the best collaborator forever. 我们永远是最好的合作伙伴. 3. A far better approach is to use an outsider as a collaborator. 比较恰当的方法是，跟这些外部专家合作。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('strict', '[strɪkt]', 'adj.严格的；精确的；完全的', '1. Our manager is very strict with us. 我们的经理对我们要求很严格。 2. There are strict controls on immigration into this country. 移民到这个国家有严格的限制。 3. Anything you tell us is in the strictest confidence. 你告诉我们的都是绝密信息。 4. Don\'t worry about that; he is a man with strict loyalty. 不用担心那一点,他是一个绝对忠诚的人。', '副词: strictly 比较级: stricter 最高级: strictest 名词: strictness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('discourse', '[\'dɪskɔːrs]', 'n.谈话，讨论；（一系列的）演讲，文章 vi.讲述；谈话 vt.叙述；讨论', '1. The judges had solemn discourse together. 法官们在一起严肃地交谈。 2. They listened to his discourse on human relations. 他们听他作关于人际关系的演讲。 3. He discoursed impressively on Newton\'s theory of gravity. 他讲述了牛顿的引力定律，给人以深刻的印象。 4. The teacher is discoursing with him. 老师正在和他谈话。 5. The old man discoursed his experiences when he was a child. 这位老人叙述了他孩子时的经历。', '名词: discourser 过去式: discoursed 过去分词: discoursed 现在分词: discoursing 第三人称单数: discourses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('employee', '[ɪm\'plɔɪiː]', 'n.雇员', '1. This employee was dismissed for laziness. 这名雇员因为懒惰而被解雇。 2. Their situations are now reversed as employee has become employer. 他们双方的地位转换了，雇员成了雇主。 3. The boss struck off 100 dollars from the salary of the employee as fine. 老板从这个雇员的工资里扣除100美元作为罚款。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('forestall', '[fɔːr\'stɔːl]', 'v.领先；占先一步；先发制人，阻止，妨碍', '1. She forestalled my plan to meet her. 她抢在我前面，使我要去接她的计划落了空。 2. I have my objection all prepared,but Stephens forestall me. 我已做好准备要提出反对意见，不料斯蒂芬斯却抢先了一步。 3. We must act now to forestall disaster. 我们现在必须采取行动以防灾难。 4. We installed an alarm system to forestall break-in. 我们安装了一套警报系统来预防小偷的闯入。', '名词: forestaller 过去式: forestalled 过去分词: forestalled 现在分词: forestalling 第三人称单数: forestalls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('delicious', '[dɪ\'lɪʃəs]', 'adj.美味的；可口的', '1. She can produce delicious meal from very simple ingredients. 她能用简单配料烹调出美味的饭菜。 2. The hunter entertained us with venison which was very delicious. 猎人拿出了非常美味的鹿肉招待我们。 3. The bannock is delicious. 这种薄饼很可口。 4. I like the delicious salad of crisp lettuce and tomatos. 我喜欢这种脆莴苣和番茄做的沙拉，很好吃。', '副词: deliciously 名词: deliciousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rigor', '[\'rɪgə]', 'n.严格；严厉；严酷；艰苦；严密；精确；[医]寒战；僵直；强直', '1. The crime will be treated with the full rigor of the law. 这一罪行会严格依法审理。 2. The expedition suffered all the rigors of a Canadian winter. 这支探险队饱受了加拿大严冬的折磨。 3. It shows the rigor of a scientific proof. 这体现了科学实证的严密。 4. Rigor mortis had already set in. 尸体已经僵硬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deleterious', '[ˌdelə\'tɪriəs]', 'adj.有害的', '1. This food be deleterious to health . 这食物有害健康。 2. Such weather is deleterious on plants. 这种天气对植物有害。 3. Some drugs have a deleterious effect on the body. 有些药品对身体有害', '副词: deleteriously 名词: deleteriousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('liberal', '[\'lɪbərəl]', 'adj.慷慨的；大方的；开明的；自由主义的 n.自由主义者；开明的人', '1. They are liberal in their help. 他们慷慨相助。 2. She is liberal with her money. 她用钱大方。 3. Her parents are very liberal and allow her a lot of freedom. 她的父母很开明，让她享有许多的自由。 4. The headmaster has liberal views about what his pupils should wear. 校长对他的学生应穿什么服装这一点持开明的态度。 5. He is an open-minded liberal. 他是一个开明的自由主义者。', '副词: liberally 名词: liberalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('minor', '[\'maɪnər]', 'adj.轻微的；较小的；次要的 n.未成年人；辅修科目；[音]小调 v.辅修', '1. You should be thankful that you have escaped with only minor injuries. 你应该感到庆幸,你只是受了点轻伤,但是却脱险了。 2. We can only make minor concessions, but it might break the deadlock. 我们只能做些较小的让步，但这就可能打破僵局。 3. She played a minor role in the movie. 她在电影中扮演了一个次要的角色。 4. It is illegal to sell cigarettes to minors. 向未成年人出售香烟是违法的。 5. Many university students will minor in some practical courses. 许多大学生都会副修一些实用性的课程。', '过去式: minored 过去分词: minored 现在分词: minoring 第三人称单数: minors');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('viable', '[\'vaɪəbl]', 'adj.能生存的；可行的', '1. How can philosophy of education be both viable and good? 为何教育哲学能够独立生存并且很好地发展? 2. The economy of the country is not viable. 这个国家经济是难以维持的。 3. The human fetus usually becomes viable by the end of the seventh month. 人的胎儿通常在第七个月末产下后可以自然存活。 4. The scheme is economically viable. 这个计划从经济效益来看是可行的。', '副词: viably 名词: viability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('artificial', '[ˌɑːrtɪ\'fɪʃl]', 'adj.人造的；虚伪的；武断的', '1. This orange drink contains no artificial flavourings. 这种橙汁饮品不含人工调味料。 2. This dress is made of artificial fibers. 这件衣服是人造纤维的。 3. She welcomed us with an artificial smile on her face. 她脸上挂着虚委的笑容来迎接我们。 4. Her artificial manner made me sick. 她那装腔作势的样子令我恶心。', '副词: artificially 名词: artificiality');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('malign', '[mə\'laɪn]', 'adj.有害的；恶性的；有恶意的 v.诽谤；中伤；说坏话', '1. A malign tumour was found in his stomach. 在他的胃部发现了一个恶性肿瘤。　 2. Malign fate had broken their necks, perhaps, but never their hearts. 致命的厄运有时期断了他们的头颈，但从不曾扼杀他们的勇气。 3. She likes to malign innocent persons. 她爱诋毁那些清白的人。 4. You malign a generous person when you call him a stingy person. 当你说一个慷慨的人吝啬时，你是在诋毁他。', '副词: malignly 名词: maligner 过去式: maligned 过去分词: maligned 现在分词: maligning 第三人称单数: maligns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pact', '[pækt]', 'n.契约；协定；条约', '1. It was a pact made in fun long ago. 这是很久以前在开玩笑时定下的契约。 2. Tell Me Why You and I must make a pact. 你和我必须订立契约。 3. They made a pact not to tell anyone. 他们有协定，不告诉任何人。 4. They ratify the pact because they think it will bring peace. 他们批准了这项协定，因为他们认为它将能带来和平。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avert', '[ə\'vɜːrt]', 'vt.转开；避免；防止', '1. It was Scott\'s turn to avert his gaze. 这下轮到斯科特移开他注视的目光了。 2. The government has failed to avert a national strike. 政府没有能够避免这场全国性的罢工。 3. He managed to avert suspicion. 他设法避嫌。 4. The lake will be dyked to avert floods. 将为此湖筑堤以防洪水。', '形容词: avertible 过去式: averted 过去分词: averted 现在分词: averting 第三人称单数: averts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('facilitate', '[fə\'sɪlɪteɪt]', 'vt.促进；帮助；使 ... 容易', '1. Friendly contacts between different peoples facilitate the cultural and economic interchange. 各国人民的友好接触促进文化和经济交流。 2. We facilitate them to resist the enemy. 我们帮助他们与敌人对抗。 3. The new underground railway will facilitate the journey to all parts of the city. 新的地下铁路将为去城市各处提供方便。', '形容词: facilitative 名词: facilitator 过去式: facilitated 过去分词: facilitated 现在分词: facilitating 第三人称单数: facilitates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nationality', '[ˌnæʃə\'næləti]', 'n.国籍；民族', '1. She has dual nationality. 她有双重国籍。 2. She storied about her nationality. 她谎报自己的国籍。 3. There are two main nationalities in our village. 我们村子有两大民族。 4. The nation will combat all invaders. 这个民族将同所有的入侵者战斗。', '名词复数: nationalities');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('clergy', '[\'klɜːrdʒi]', 'n.[总称]牧师；神职人员', '1. The clergy were sacred beings in Miss Ainley\'s eyes. 在安利小姐看来，牧师都是圣人。 2. I could heartily wish that more of our country clergy would follow this example. 我衷心希望，我国有更多的牧师效法这个榜样。 3. Prior to the law\'s enactment, most of the Danish clergy opposed it. 在通过该法规之前，多数丹麦神职人员反对此法规。 4. The superior clergy and a small remnant of other educated men read and wrote Latin. 上等的神职人员和一小部分残余的其他受过教育的人使用拉丁语读写。', '名词复数: clergies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arithmetic', '[ə\'rɪθmətɪk]', 'n.算术；计算 adj.算术的', '1. I\'m good at history but not so hot at arithmetic. 我的历史成绩不错，但算术不太好。 2. He got the answer by mental arithmetic. 他用心算得出了答案。 3. My job is to instruct you in arithmetic. 我的工作就是指导你学算术。 4. I am not sure my arithmetic is correct, but I think the total is 75. 我不确定我的计算是不是正确,但是我认为总数是75。 5. I saw him puzzle over an arithmetic problem. 我看见他正在苦心思索一道算术题。', '形容词: arithmetical 副词: arithmetically 名词: arithmetician');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diagnose', '[ˌdaɪəɡ\'noʊs]', 'v.判断；诊断(疾病)', '1. Geological investigations must correctly diagnose a specific soil-like condition. 地质调查必须正确地判断出明确的土状条件。 2. What more will you want to know to diagnose this problem? 要弄清这个问题，你还需要知道些什么? 3. The book diagnoses our present economic ills. 这本书切中了我们现在经济的时弊。 4. The test is used to diagnose a variety of diseases. 此项化验可用于诊断多种疾病。', '形容词: diagnosable 过去式: diagnosed 过去分词: diagnosed 现在分词: diagnosing 第三人称单数: diagnoses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('active', '[\'æktɪv]', 'adj.活跃的；积极的；起作用的；灵活的', '1. Ms. Brown is active in the party. 布朗女士在晚会上很活跃。 2. He is an active member of the school\'s stamp club. 他是学校集邮俱乐部的一名活跃会员。 3. She was active as a left-winger in the party. 她是党内积极的左翼分子。 4. We should take active part in extracurricular activities. 我们应该积极参加课外活动。', '副词: actively 名词: activeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('misery', '[\'mɪzəri]', 'n.痛苦；悲惨的境遇；苦难', '1. War necessarily causes misery and waste. 战争必然造成痛苦和破坏。 2. He was doomed to undergo another misery. 他注定要经历另一场痛苦。 3. One usually associates poverty with misery. 人们一说到贫穷，常常就联想起悲惨的境遇。 4. He endured agonies of loneliness and misery. 他忍受着寂寞和贫穷的折磨。', '名词复数: miseries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deadly', '[\'dedli]', 'adj.致命的；如死一样的 adv.非常地；如死一般地', '1. Cancer is a deadly disease. 癌症是一种致命的疾病。 2. Fog is the sailor\'s deadly enemy. 雾是航海者最致命的敌人。 3. The accident subjected her to a deadly blow. 这次意外使她受到致命的打击。 4. The conference was deadly dull. 会议开得死气沉沉的。 5. Mary is finding life deadly monotonous . 玛丽感到生活非常单调。', '比较级: deadlier 最高级: deadliest 名词: deadliness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('messy', '[\'mesi]', 'adj.散乱的；污秽的；麻烦的', '1. I can\'t find anything on this messy desk. 在这张堆放得乱七八糟的桌子上我什么也找不到。 2. She doesn\'t know how to tidy up the messy room. 她不知道该怎样整理这个凌乱的房间。 3. It is shaping up to be a dirty, messy campaign. 这绝对会成为一场卑鄙而肮脏的竞选。 4. The divorce was painful and messy. 那次离婚令人痛苦而又纠葛不清。', '副词: messily 比较级: messier 最高级: messiest 名词: messiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('maximum', '[\'mæksɪməm]', 'n.最大量；最大限度；最高点 adj.最高的；最大极限的', '1. This hall holds a maximum of seventy people. 这厅最多容纳七十人。 2. The child turned the volume up to the maximum. 小孩把音量转到了最大。 3. It is the maximum the insurance company will pay. 这是保险公司所能付给的最大金额。 4. Our goal is to achieve the maximum of efficiency. 我们的目标是取得最高的效率。 5. The maximum price we can pay is 50 pence per yard. 我们所能出的最高价格是每码50便士。', '名词复数: maximums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nibble', '[\'nɪbl]', 'v.一点点地咬；轻咬；吹毛求疵；（审慎地）表示有意接受 n.轻咬；少量', '1. He didn\'t answer, but just continued to nibble at his food. 他没有回答，只是继续一点一点地吃东西。 2. The mice have nibbled a hole in the cheese. 老鼠在奶酪上啃出了一个洞。 3. Food and rent nibbled away at the money they had saved. 花在食物和房租上的钱把他们的积蓄一点一点耗掉了。 4. She nibbled his ears playfully. 她轻轻咬他的耳朵玩。 5. I feel a nibble on the end of my line. 我觉得有鱼轻轻地咬钩。', '过去式: nibbled 过去分词: nibbled 现在分词: nibbling 第三人称单数: nibbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('withstand', '[wɪð\'stænd]', 'vt.对抗；经得起；承受', '1. He slew all who dared to withstand him. 他把敢于对抗他的人都斩尽杀绝。 2. Explorers have to withstand hardships. 探险者得忍受艰苦。 3. They could not withstand the fierceness of attack of those soldiers. 他们抵挡不住那些士兵猛烈的进攻。 4. This dress material will withstand repeated washing. 这种衣料经得住反复洗涤。', '名词: withstander 过去式: withstood 过去分词: withstood 现在分词: withstanding 第三人称单数: withstands');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('monster', '[\'mɑːnstər]', 'n.怪物；恶人；巨物 adj.巨大的；庞大的', '1. A hideous monster attacked the helpless villagers. 有个丑恶的怪物袭击了手无寸铁的村民。 2. I saw a horrible monster in the forest. 我在林中见到一头可怕的怪物。 3. The judge told the murderer that he was a monster. 法官对凶手说他是一个穷凶极恶的人。 4. He\'s a lovely man, but when he gets jealous he turns into a monster. 他是个讨人喜欢的人,但是当他嫉妒起来时,就成了一个恶魔。 5. Many monster high-rise buildings spring up all over the city. 许多巨大的高层建筑在这座城市拔地而起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('acclaim', '[ə\'kleɪm]', 'n.喝采；欢呼；赞同 v.欢呼；喝采；称赞', '1. Her performance won her much critical acclaim. 她的表演大获评论界赞颂。 2. He was welcomed with great acclaim. 他受到十分热烈的欢迎。 3. Every four years such acclaim would echo. 这种欢呼，每四年都会来一次。 4. The novel received great acclaim. 这本小说备受赞扬。 5. The whole city turned out to acclaim the winning team. 人们倾城而出为获胜的队欢呼喝彩。', '名词: acclaimer 过去式: acclaimed 过去分词: acclaimed 现在分词: acclaiming 第三人称单数: acclaims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hawk', '[hɔːk]', 'n.鹰；鹰派人物、主战分子；贪婪的人；清嗓 v.沿街叫卖；散布；鹰扑；放鹰行猎；清嗓', '1. The hawk is hovering overhead. 鹰在头顶上盘旋。 2. The hawk pounced on its prey and carried it off. 那只鹰向那小动物猛扑过去把它叼走了。 3. He is neither a dove nor a hawk, but betwixt and between. 他既不是鸽派，也不是鹰派，而是中间派。 4. In a free market, retailers hawk their wares. 自由市场里商贩们不停地叫卖着。', '形容词: hawkish 副词: hawkishly 名词: hawkishness 过去式: hawked 过去分词: hawked 现在分词: hawking 第三人称单数: hawks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('evade', '[ɪ\'veɪd]', 'v.逃避；躲避；规避', '1. He could not evade the law. 他逃避不了法律。 2. They evade paying taxes by living abroad. 他们住在国外以逃避交税。 3. In order to evade the persecution of fascists, he had to escape abroad. 为躲避法西斯的迫害，他不得不流徙到国外。 4. Give me a direct answer, and stop evade the issue. 给我一个直截了当的回答，不要回避这一问题。', '形容词: evadable 名词: evader 过去式: evaded 过去分词: evaded 现在分词: evading 第三人称单数: evades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incessant', '[ɪn\'sesnt]', 'adj.不断的；无尽的', '1. The incessant barking of the dog annoyed me. 不断的狗叫声让我苦恼。 2. We felt put out by the guest\'s incessant requests. 客人不断的要求令我们觉得受打扰。', '副词: incessantly 名词: incessancy');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('topsoil', '[\'tɑːpsɔɪl]', 'n.表层土 v.去掉表土', '1. Heavy rains washed the topsoil away. 大雨把表层土冲蚀掉了 2. This topsoil tends to wash away. 表层土壤要冲掉了。', '过去式: topsoiled 过去分词: topsoiled 现在分词: topsoiling 第三人称单数: topsoils');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plate', '[pleɪt]', 'n.碟；金属板；板块；盘 vt.电镀；用金属板固定；为 ... 制印版；给 ... 装钢板', '1. Just a paper? It\'s a small plate of dish. 不就是一篇论文吗,小菜一碟。 2. The doctor inserted a steel plate into his damaged leg. 医生在他受伤的腿中植入了一块钢板。 3. This is apparently related to the tectonic setting of Shandong,namely, the continental margin where the Pacific Plate collided against the Eurasian Plate. 之所以如此,显然与山东所处的大地构造位置,即太平洋板块与欧亚板块相互碰撞的陆缘地带密切相关。 4. He put the apples on a round plate. 他把苹果放在一个圆盘子里。 5. He wanted to plate copper with silver. 他想给铜容器镀银。', '名词: plater 过去式: plated 过去分词: plated 现在分词: plating 第三人称单数: plates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allegiance', '[ə\'liːdʒəns]', 'n.忠诚；效忠', '1. The judge received their oath of allegiance. 法官听取了他们的忠诚誓言。 2. Private members keep up their outward allegiance to the parties they belong to. 议员们对各自所属的党派保持表面上的忠诚。 3. His allegiance has never been questioned. 他的忠心是毫无疑问的。 4. The soldiers swore allegiance to their motherland. 士兵们宣誓效忠于他们的祖国。', '形容词: allegiant');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('brim', '[brɪm]', 'n.边；边缘 v.（装）满；（使）溢出', '1. He drank at the fountain\'s brim. 他醉在喷泉边。 2. The heart-shaped brim and brown velvet ribbon around the hat add a lovel accent. 心形边和褐色丝绒带周围的帽子向勒沃尔口音。 3. Nevertheless, the brim part of design is not very ideal. 不外，图案的边缘部门不是很完美。 4. With a dim triumph, she trims the swimming-suit rim at the swimming-pool brim. 她带着暗淡的喜悦在泳池边整理泳装的边缘。 5. The tea cup was filled to the brim. 茶杯满到杯子边了。', '过去式: brimmed 过去分词: brimmed 现在分词: brimming 第三人称单数: brims');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('universe', '[\'juːnɪvɜːrs]', 'n.宇宙；万物；世界', '1. The universe exists in space. 宇宙存在于太空。 2. The depth of the universe is immeasurable. 宇宙无限深广。 3. The Earth is only one of the numerous planets in the universe. 地球只是宇宙中众多星球中的一个。 4. Man is the soul of the universe. 人是万物之灵。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annoy', '[ə\'nɔɪ]', 'v.使恼怒；使烦恼；骚扰', '1. We can annoy the enemy by raids. 我们可用袭击骚扰敌人。 2. Some peoples\' daily mission is to annoy you! 一些人的日常使命就是骚扰你！', '过去式: annoyed 过去分词: annoyed 现在分词: annoying 第三人称单数: annoys');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cartilage', '[\'kɑːrtɪlɪdʒ]', 'n.软骨', '1. The cartilage in such areas is almost inextensible. 这些部位的软骨几乎一点儿也不能伸展。 2. Cartilage serves as a supporting framework for softer tissues. 软骨对于软组织起到一种支持框架作用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('physiology', '[ˌfɪzi\'ɑːlədʒi]', 'n.生理学；生理机能', '1. We had studied physiology in middle school. 我在中学就已经学过生理学。 2. She knows physiology from beginning to end. 她对生理学这门学科了如指掌。 3. Physiology maturity is grow as body functionary and mature. 生理成熟是随着身体机能的生长而成熟。 4. Clothing is one of the most basic human physiology. 衣是人类最基本的生理需求之一。', '名词: physiologist');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('illegitimate', '[ˌɪlə\'dʒɪtəmət]', 'adj.非法的；私生的；不合规则的', '1. The agency made illegitimate use of public funds. 这个机构非法动用公款。 2. Perhaps she was an illegitimate daughter. 也许她是个私生女。 3. He was discarded as an illegitimate child. 他被当作私生子抛弃了。 4. In this sentence the writer uses an illegitimate construction. 作者在这个句子中用了不符合语法的结构。', '副词: illegitimately');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('organic', '[ɔːr\'ɡænɪk]', 'adj.器官的；有机的；有组织的；根本的；接近自然的 n.有机物质', '1. The illness is organic in origin. 该病起初是器质性疾患。 2. I am not good at organic chemistry. 我的有机化学学得不好。 3. You can apply heat to decompose organic compounds. 你可以加热来分解有机化合物。 4. The music is organic to the story. 这首乐曲是这个故事必不可少的组成部分。 5. Oil-yielding organic matter is contained in the shales. 在这些页岩里有产油的有机物质。', '副词: organically 名词: organicity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('quarter', '[\'kwɔːrtər]', 'n.四分之一；一刻钟；一季；25美分；区；方向 v.四等分 adj.四分之一的', '1. Only a quarter of the earth is land. 仅仅地球的四分之一是陆地。 2. It\'s a quarter past ten. 现在是十点一刻。 3. The flight was put off about a quarter, because of ground fog. 由于地面有雾，这次班机推迟1 刻钟。 4. The rent is due at the end of each quarter. 缴纳租金以每季度末为期限。 5. We should quarter a pineapple. 我们应该把这个菠萝分成四等份。', '过去式: quartered 过去分词: quartered 现在分词: quartering 第三人称单数: quarters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beget', '[bɪ\'ɡet]', 'v.产生；引起；生(子女)', '1. Great love will beget great faith. 大的爱就产生大的信心。 2. Life on Earth alters Earth to beget more life. 地球上的生命改变着地球以产生更多的生命。 3. It may be that stable environments beget diversity because they allow rare species to persist. 可能是稳定的环境引起差异，因为他们允许稀有物种存留。 4. I were going to beget a child knowing that the child was going to be a homicidal maniac. 我明明知道自己的孩子将成为杀人疯子还要把孩子生出来。', '名词: begetter 过去式: begot 过去分词: begotten/begot 现在分词: begetting 第三人称单数: begets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('expedition', '[ˌekspə\'dɪʃn]', 'n.远征；探险队；迅速', '1. They equipped themselves for the expedition. 他们为远征治装。 2. They planned to organize a scientific expedition. 他们计划组织一次科学考察。 3. He is the commander of the expedition. 他是探险队的队长。 4. The expedition suffered all the rigors of a Canadian winter. 这支探险队饱受了加拿大严冬的折磨。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sac', '[sæk]', 'n.囊；液囊', '1. The peritoneal cavity is a closed sac. 腹膜腔是一个封闭的囊腔。 2. The yolk sac is gradually vascularized. 卵黄囊逐渐被血管化了。 3. These abnormalities would cause the abnormal structure of mature embryo sac. 这些异常可能最终导致多种结构异常成熟胚囊的形成。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lizard', '[\'lɪzərd]', 'n.蜥蜴', '1. Lizards have four legs and a long tail. 蜥蜴有四条腿和一条长尾巴。 2. Lizards and snakes are cold-blooded animals. 蜥蜴和蛇是冷血动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('devious', '[\'diːviəs]', 'adj.迂回的；弯曲的；不正直的；狡猾的', '1. The coach followed a rather devious course to its destination. 长途汽车要绕很多弯路才到达目的地。 2. Let\'s take the devious route home to avoid the crowds in the main roads. 为了避免大街上的拥挤，我们还是绕道回家去吧。 3. Go along the lotus pond, it is a devious road. 沿着荷塘，是一条曲折的小煤屑路。 4. His devious nature was shown in half lies and small dishonesties. 他不正直的天性表现在小谎话及细小的不诚实行为中。', '副词: deviously 名词: deviousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('underscore', '[ˌʌndər\'skɔːr]', 'vt.划线于；强调；提供伴奏乐 n.下划线；影片伴奏乐', '1. Let me underscore two of many reasons for this concern. 值得担忧的原因很多，让我着重说明其中两点。 2. Please underscore the word three times for emphasis. 为了强调起见，请在该词下面划三条线。 3. Let me underscore that you should focus on an important problem. 让我强调一下：你必须关注于某一重要问题。 4. These results underscore the importance of context in studies of social capital. 这些结果强调了社会资本研究中环境的重要性。 5. They must begin with a letter or the underscore character 开始部分必须为一个字母或是下划线', '过去式: underscored 过去分词: underscored 现在分词: underscoring 第三人称单数: underscores');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dormitory', '[\'dɔːrmətɔːri]', 'n.集体宿舍 n.【美】学生宿舍楼', '1. He hangs out in the school dormitory. 他留在学校的宿舍里。 2. Every girl must sign in when she comes back to the dormitory. 每个女生回到宿舍的时候都必须签到。 3. He soon gets accustomed to dormitory life and make two or three friend. 他不久就逐渐习惯了宿舍的生活并交了两三个朋友。 4. Every dormitory houses 200 students. 每一栋宿舍能容纳200个学生。', '名词复数: dormitories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('weather', '[\'weðər]', 'n.天气；气象；境遇 vt.使风化；经受住；使日晒雨淋 vi.风化；褪色；经受风雨 adj.上风的；天气预报的', '1. What is the weather like today? 今天天气情况怎样？ 2. The meteorologist drew a picture of the weather. 气象学者画了一张气象图。 3. The past years had known him in many weathers. 过去的岁月里,他起起落落。 4. The rocks on the mountain have to be weathered by wind and water. 山上的岩石得经受风化和水蚀。 5. The paint on the walls had weathered. 墙壁上的涂料已经风干了。 6. Fill in the form below about the weather report. 续下面关于天气预报的表格。', '过去式: weathered 过去分词: weathered 现在分词: weathering 第三人称单数: weathers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opposite', '[\'ɑːpəzət]', 'adj.相反的；对面的；对立的 prep.在 ... 对面；演对手戏 adv.在对面地；处于相反位置地 n.对立物；对立者；对手', '1. She hurried away in the opposite direction. 她朝着相反的方向匆匆离去了。 2. The fireplace flamed the opposite wall. 炉火照亮了对面的墙壁。 3. Our points of view are at opposite poles. 我们的观点截然相反。 4. He came in and took a seat opposite to me. 他走进来，坐在我对面的座位上。 5. They sat opposite at the table. 他们面对面地坐在桌子两旁 6. Vice and virtue are opposites. 善和恶是对立面。', '副词: oppositely 名词: oppositeness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ignition', '[ɪɡ\'nɪʃn]', 'n.点火；点火器；[化]灼热；[机]发火装置', '1. Would you please turn off the car ignition? 请你把汽车的点火装置关掉好吗? 2. He fumbled the key into the ignition. 他笨拙地把钥匙插进汽车点火开关。 3. I must have left my key in the ignition. 我肯定是把车钥匙忘在点火开关上了。 4. Write the selected music and ignition control programs into the igniter. 将选定的曲目的音乐及点火控制程序写入点火器中。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ruminate', '[\'ruːmɪneɪt]', 'v.深思；沉思；反刍', '1. The discovery provides pabulum for the scientific community to ruminate on for decades to come. 这项发现为科学界对未来十年的深思提供了精神食粮。 2. The cow began to ruminate after eating up grass. 牛吃完草后开始反刍。', '形容词: ruminative 副词: ruminatively 名词: ruminator 过去式: ruminated 过去分词: ruminated 现在分词: ruminating 第三人称单数: ruminates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crazy', '[\'kreɪzi]', 'adj.疯狂的；荒唐的；着迷的 n.荒唐的人 adv.疯狂地', '1. Are you crazy? 你疯了吗？ 2. It drives me crazy. 它使我快要发疯了。 3. The mother of the kidnapped child was crazy with worry. 那个被绑架的孩子的母亲担心得几乎发狂了。 4. What started him off on this crazy idea? 他这个荒唐的主意是哪儿来的?', '副词: crazily 比较级: crazier 最高级: craziest 名词: craziness 名词复数: crazies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resolute', '[\'rezəluːt]', 'adj.坚决的；果断的', '1. He was resolute in carrying out his plan. 他执行起计划来是非常坚决的。 2. He is a person with graceful manner and resolute action. 他是个举止文雅但行动坚决的人。 3. We must take immediate and resolute action. 我们必须采取坚决果断的行动。 4. He curbed it, I think, as a resolute rider would curb a rearing steed. 我想，他还是管住了它，就象一个果断的骑师管住一匹用后腿站立起来的骏马。', '副词: resolutely 名词: resoluteness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('navigate', '[\'nævɪɡeɪt]', 'vi.航行；驾驶；操纵 vt.航行；驾驶；横渡；<口>设法穿过，走过，经过', '1. The river became too narrow and shallow to navigate. 河道变得又窄又浅，无法航行。 2. Many captains depend on electronic devices to navigate their ships. 许多船长依靠电子仪器来驾驶他们的船。 3. Hyperlinks make it much easier to navigate through a document. 超链接使到你在文档中更容易的操纵。 4. The large ship could not navigate the river. 那艘大轮船不能在河里航行。', '过去式: navigated 过去分词: navigated 现在分词: navigating 第三人称单数: navigates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('eyewitness', '[\'aɪwɪtnəs]', 'n.目击者；见证人', '1. He was the only eyewitness of the robbery. 他是那起抢劫案的唯一目击者。 2. One eyewitness is better than ten earwitnesses. 一人目击，胜过十人听到。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('solder', '[\'sɑːdər]', 'n.焊接剂；接合物 v.焊接', '1. Generally the same fluxes will work for lead-free solder. 一般来说,相同的焊剂用于无铅焊料是有效的。 2. An ideal connection that puts any solder to shame. 这种理想的连结方式，让其它各类接合方式瞠乎其后。 3. He soldered the wire back on. 他把金属丝重新焊上去了。 4. Surface to solder are gold and clean. 待焊接的表面是清洁的金面。', '名词: solderer 过去式: soldered 过去分词: soldered 现在分词: soldering 第三人称单数: solders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('saddle', '[\'sædl]', 'n.鞍；车座；山脊；当权 vt.装以马鞍；使负担 vi.装马鞍', '1. The jockey vaulted into the saddle . 骑士一跃而跨坐鞍上。 2. The saddle galled the horse\'s back. 马鞍擦伤了马背。 3. The bicycle saddle is too high for this child. 这辆自行车车座对这孩子来说太高了。 4. He is determined to stay in the saddle at all cost. 他打定主意要不惜一切代价继续掌权。 5. I had to saddle for him the first few times. 头几次我得替他套马鞍。 6. He saddled up his horse and rode away. 他给马装上鞍子便骑马离去了。', '过去式: saddled 过去分词: saddled 现在分词: saddling 第三人称单数: saddles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('provision', '[prə\'vɪʒn]', 'n.食品；粮食；供应；规定；条款；预备；【经】准备金 vt.向 ... 供应食物', '1. We set out with enough provisions. 我们带上足够的食品出发了。 2. Provision of shelter was the Red Crosss main concern for the disaster victims. 为灾民提供避难处是 红十字会的主要工作。 3. The present law makes no provision for this. 现行的法律对此未作任何规定。 4. Both sides should act according to the provisions of the agreement. 双方都应按协议条款办事。 5. They provisioned the ship for a long voyage. 他们为远航的船只准备了食品和必需品。', '名词: provisioner 过去式: provisioned 过去分词: provisioned 现在分词: provisioning 第三人称单数: provisions');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diet', '[\'daɪət]', 'n.日常食物；规定饮食；节食 n.（日本等国的）国会 v.节食；照规定饮食；喂食', '1. Too rich a diet (ie Too much rich food) is not good for you. 吃太多油腻的食物对你身体不好。 2. You should eat more high-protein diet. 你应该多吃些高蛋白食物。 3. Her diet restricts her to 1500 calories a day. 她的规定饮食限制她每天摄入1500卡的热量。 4. The doctor says I\'ve got to go on a diet. 医生说我得节食。 5. The Diet will have a long session. 国会将有长会期。 6. You ought to diet and take more exercise. 你应该节食并多做运动。', '名词: dieter 过去式: dieted 过去分词: dieted 现在分词: dieting 第三人称单数: diets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('curve', '[kɜːrv]', 'n.曲线；弯曲；弯曲物；弧线', '1. His plane swooped a beautiful curve up and down. 他的飞机在上下翻飞时画出了一条美丽的曲线。 2. The stairs ascended in a graceful curve. 楼梯以优美的曲线上升。 3. His spine developed a slight curve. 他的脊柱有点弯曲。 4. The car made a sharp curve. 汽车拐了一个急弯。', '形容词: curvy 名词: curvedness 过去式: curved 过去分词: curved 现在分词: curving 第三人称单数: curves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('continent', '[\'kɒntɪnənt]', 'n.大陆；洲；(the Continent)欧洲大陆', '1. The discovery of the new continent is usually referred to Columbus. 人们通常认为新大陆是哥伦布发现的。 2. There are seven continents in the world. 世界上有七大洲。 3. Asia is the largest continent on Earth. 亚洲是地球上最大的洲。 4. Many people embark at Dover for the Continent. 许多前往欧洲大陆的人都在多佛搭船。', '副词: continently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('orchestra', '[\'ɔːrkɪstrə]', 'n.管弦乐队', '1. The orchestra tuned their instruments. 乐队在给乐器调音。 2. The orchestra has several concert engagements. 这管弦乐队已安排好几场音乐会。 3. This orchestra has been established under the patronage of the government. 这个交响乐团是在政府赞助下成立的。', '形容词: orchestral 副词: orchestrally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crave', '[kreɪv]', 'v.渴望；热望；迫切需要；恳求', '1. Many young children crave attention. 许多小孩子渴望得到关心。 2. All Americans crave to be svelte (and rich). 所有的美国人都渴望身材苗条(和富有)。 3. By this time the inner man began to crave nourishment. 到这个时候，肚子开始咕咕叫着要吃东西了。 4. I crave that we may taste of your wine. 我恳求让我们尝尝您的酒。', '副词: cravingly 名词: craver 过去式: craved 过去分词: craved 现在分词: craving 第三人称单数: craves');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apt', '[æpt]', 'adj.恰当的；聪明的；易于 ... 的 abbr.公寓（=apartment） abbr.才能；天资（=aptitude）', '1. In many ways, the comparison is apt. 在诸多方面，这个对比是恰当的。 2. I imagine that you may deduce an apt moral from my tale. 我觉得你也许能从我的际遇中引出恰当的教训。 3. Henry is an apt student of the practical science. 亨利在实践科学上是个聪明的学生。 4. He is a clever boy but apt to get into mischief. 他是个聪明却很调皮的孩子。 5. He has a handful of intelligent and apt students. 他有许多天资聪颖的学生。', '副词: aptly 名词: aptness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suppress', '[sə\'pres]', 'vt.镇压；隐瞒；压制；止住；禁止', '1. The revolt was suppressed in a matter of hours. 叛乱在几小时之内就镇压下去了。 2. All these movements were suppressed by the warlord government. 所有这些运动都受到军阀政府的镇压。 3. A common person would not suppress his real name. 一个平常人是不会隐瞒他的真实姓名的。 4. He couldn\'t suppress his anger. 他简直怒不可遏。', '形容词: suppressible 名词: suppressant 过去式: suppressed 过去分词: suppressed 现在分词: suppressing 第三人称单数: suppresses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('typical', '[\'tɪpɪkl]', 'adj.特有的；典型的；有代表性的', '1. Since I\'m here, I\'d like to try a typical dish of this country. 既然来了，我想吃这个国家特有的食物。 2. If they reappear, they manifest themselves in certain typical ways. 一旦它们重复出现就会以特有的方法表现出来。 3. This is a typical bourgeois neighborhood. 这是一个典型的中产阶级地区。 4. They reacted to the appalling weather with typical British stoicism. 他们忍受着恶劣天气的煎熬,表现了英国人典型的坚韧不拔的精神。', '副词: typically 名词: typicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('byword', '[\'baɪwɜːrd]', 'n.代名词；笑柄；谚语；俗语', '1. The soldier\'s name was a byword for bravery. 那个战士的名字是勇敢的代名词。 2. She became the byword of the village. 她成了村中的笑柄。 3. Caution becomes a byword for investors. 小心谨慎成为了投资者的谚语。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enumerate', '[ɪ\'nuːməreɪt]', 'vt.数；列举；枚举', '1. We found more children at the circus than we could enumerate. 我们见到数不清的孩子在看马戏。 2. Can you enumerate the capitals of the50 states? 你能把五十州的首府列举出来吗？ 3. Let me enumerate many flaws in your hypothesis. 让我列举你前提中的许多谬误。 4. Provide the path of the root folder to enumerate. 提供要枚举的根文件夹的路径。', '形容词: enumerative 名词: enumeration 过去式: enumerated 过去分词: enumerated 现在分词: enumerating 第三人称单数: enumerates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('genetic', '[dʒə\'netɪk]', 'adj.遗传的；基因的；起源的', '1. He chose genetic engineering to be his lifelong career. 他选择了遗传工程学作为终生的事业。 2. Most chromomeres contain a genetic unit. 绝大多数染色粒包含一个遗传单位。 3. The disease is caused by a genetic defect. 这种疾病的起因是基因缺陷。 4. Every living thing has its own genetic chips. 每种生物都有自己的基因芯片。', '副词: genetically 异体字: genetical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('admire', '[əd\'maɪər]', 'vt.钦佩；赞美；羡慕；欣赏', '1. You may not like him, but you have got to admire his persistence. 你可以不喜欢他，但你不得不佩服他那种坚韧不拔的精神。 2. We admire him for his righteousness. 我们钦佩他的正直。 3. You had better admire others more than criticize if you want to be popular. 如果你想要更受人欢迎,尽量多赞美、少批评。 4. Visitors admire Beijing for its beauty. 观光者赞赏北京的美丽。', '副词: admiringly 名词: admirer 过去式: admired 过去分词: admired 现在分词: admiring 第三人称单数: admires');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('statesman', '[\'steɪtsmən]', 'n.政治家', '1. The statesman is respected by people. 这位政治家为人们所敬重。 2. He will go down in history as a great statesman. 他将作为伟大的政治家而载入史册。', '形容词: statesmanlike 名词: statesmanship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('destructive', '[dɪ\'strʌktɪv]', 'adj.破坏性的；有害的', '1. The destructive force of the storm is huge. 暴风雨的破坏力是巨大的。 2. Are all small children so destructive? 是不是儿童都喜欢破坏? 3. Jealousy is an extremely destructive emotion. 嫉妒是一种极其破坏性的情绪。 4. A locust is a kind of destructive insect. 蝗虫是一种害虫。', '副词: destructively 名词: destructiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('allay', '[ə\'leɪ]', 'v.减轻；使 ... 缓和', '1. There pills will allay your pain. 这药丸可以减轻你的疼痛。 2. More reading may be allaying your doubt. 多读书或许可以减少你的疑惑。 3. The employer was forced to allay the tumult. 雇主被迫缓和骚乱。', '名词: allayer 过去式: allayed 过去分词: allayed 现在分词: allaying 第三人称单数: allays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indolent', '[\'ɪndələnt]', 'adj.懒惰的；慢性的', '1. I don\'t want to make friends with indolent persons. 我不喜欢和懒惰的人交朋友。 2. Those who revel in the Internet tend to lead an indolent life. 沉迷于网络的人往往过着懒散的生活。 3. Leprosy is an indolent infectious disease. 麻风病是一种顽固的传染性疾病。 4. Indolent lymphoma can have a very long duration often without the need for treatment but is not often cured. 慢性淋巴瘤通常发展期漫长并且不需要治疗，但是通常也难以治愈。', '副词: indolently');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tepid', '[\'tepɪd]', 'adj.微温的；不热心的', '1. Her feet firmly planted on the tepid rough brick of the floor. 她一双脚稳固地立在微温而粗糙的砖地上。 2. The play was greeted with tepid applause. 这台戏只得到了零落的掌声。 3. The critics\'s reaction to the film was rather tepid. 评论家对那部影片的反映不太热烈。', '副词: tepidly 名词: tepidity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bonanza', '[bə\'nænzə]', 'n.富矿带；带来好运的事物；暴富之源', '1. South Africa\'s gold and mineral bonanza is beginning to tail off . 南非的丰富黄金矿藏量以及其它矿业资源正在日益枯竭。 2. Bargain hunters enjoyed a real bonanza today. 到处买便宜货的人今天真是交了好运。 3. What a bonanza for the winning ticket holders! 对于手持胜券的人来说，这是多好的运气啊！ 4. His business was far from being a bonanza! 他的生意还没有走红运。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sanity', '[\'sænəti]', 'n.神智健全；头脑清楚', '1. We have to do it in order to keep our sanity. 我们这么做是为了保持心智健全。 2. Sanity and happiness are an impossible combination. 睿智和幸福是无法兼得的。 3. She lost her sanity when she heard of that news. 当她听到这个消息时,便发狂了。 4. Sanity of judgment has never deserted him. 他从未失去明达的判断力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abstract', '[\'æbstrækt]', 'adj.抽象的；理论的；抽象派的 n.摘要；抽象派艺术作品 v.(/æbˈstrækt/)把…抽象出；提取；抽取；转移(注意力等)；做…的摘要；<婉>偷', '1. We may talk of beautiful things, but beauty itself is abstract. 我们尽可谈论美的事物，然而美本身却是抽象的。 2. He has some abstract notion of wanting to change the world. 他有一种要改造世界的空想。 3. Abstract paintings did not appeal to him. 抽象派绘画引不起他的兴趣。 4. The whole text of the abstract shall contain not more than 300 Chinese characters. 摘要文字部分不得超过300个字。 5. She abstracted the main points from the argument. 她把论据概括成要点。', '副词: abstractly 名词: abstracter 过去式: abstracted 过去分词: abstracted 现在分词: abstracting 第三人称单数: abstracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('raw', '[rɔː]', 'adj.未加工的；生的；原始的；湿冷的 n.触到某人的痛处', '1. We imported raw rubber from Malaysia. 我们从马来西亚进口生胶。 2. Do you want your vegetables cooked or raw? 你要把蔬菜煮熟还是生吃？ 3. The factory is in frequent scarcity of raw materials. 这个工厂经常原料不足。 4. She makes use of people she meets as raw material for her fiction. 她把她所遇见的人们作为她创作小说的素材。 5. She was always ready to catch people on the raw and hold them up to ridicule. 她专爱揭短处, 挑人长相。', '副词: rawly 比较级: rawer 最高级: rawest 名词: rawness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sustenance', '[\'sʌstənəns]', 'n.维持生计；营养；食物', '1. He gave money for the sustenance of a poor family. 他把钱给一穷人家维持生活。 2. There isn\'t much sustenance in a cucumber. 黄瓜没有很多营养。 3. She is weak from lack of sustenance. 她因缺乏营养而虚弱。 4. He has gone for a week without sustenance. 他已经一星期未吃食物了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impair', '[ɪm\'per]', 'vt.损害；削弱 [计算机] 损伤.', '1. Loud noise would impair your hearing. 大的噪音会损害你的听觉。 2. Smoking can impair the sexual response. 抽烟可以削弱性反应。 3. His illness has impaired his efficiency. 生病降低了他的效率。 4. Don\'t boil the sauce as this and impair the flavor. 酱汁还要煮沸，否则会影响味道。', '名词: impairment 过去式: impaired 过去分词: impaired 现在分词: impairing 第三人称单数: impairs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ideal', '[aɪ\'diːəl]', 'adj.理想的；完美的；空想的；观念的 n.理想；典范；目标', '1. It is an ideal day for a picnic. 这是一个出外野餐的理想日子。 2. He is looking for a wife but he hasn\'t found his ideal mate. 他正在寻找未来的妻子，但还没有找到理想人选。 3. The facilities were not ideal but we managed as best we could. 设备不理想，但我们已经尽了最大的努力。 4. It\'s my ideal of what a family home should be. 这是我心目中完美的家庭住宅。 5. She \'s looking for a job, but hasn\'t found her ideal yet. 她在找工作,但是还没有找到理想的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('odor', '[\'oʊdə]', 'n.气味；名声；气息', '1. The flowers gave off a fragrant odor. 花发出一阵幽香。 2. The odor penetrated the whole room. 整个房间里弥漫着这种气味。 3. The penetrating odor of garlic soon filled the entire apartment. 大蒜刺鼻的气味很快就弥散了整个屋子 4. What he had done put him in better odor. 他的所作所为使他的名声得到改善。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('encourage', '[ɪn\'kɜːrɪdʒ]', 'vt.鼓励；促进；支持', '1. Her success encouraged me to try the same thing. 她的成功鼓励我尝试做同样的事。 2. Her parents encouraged her in her studies. 她的父母鼓励她好好学习。 3. He aims to encourage mutual understanding. 他的目的在于增进相互了解。 4. Broadband support flat salary structure, to encourage their staff to study hard. 宽带薪酬支持扁平型结构，鼓励员工努力学习。', '名词: encourager 过去式: encouraged 过去分词: encouraged 现在分词: encouraging 第三人称单数: encourages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thwart', '[θwɔːrt]', 'v.反对；阻碍 n.座板 adv.横过 adj.横向的', '1. She intends to thwart his plans, and be revenged on him. 她要破坏他的计划，以图报复。 2. Sometimes it isn\'t you I hate but your power to thwart me. 有时让我讨厌的并不是你，而是你阻挠我的能力。 3. I don\'t think that will thwart our purposes. 我认为那不会使我们的目的受到挫折。 4. Our course must thwart those designs. 我们的方针是必须挫败他们这种企图。 5. He made the fish fast to bow and stern and to the middle thwart. 他把绑鱼的绳子系在船头、船梢的中间的座板上。', '副词: thwartly 名词: thwarter 过去式: thwarted 过去分词: thwarted 现在分词: thwarting 第三人称单数: thwarts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('presume', '[prɪ\'zuːm]', 'vt.假定；推测；姑且认定；认为是理所当然 vi.越权行事；利用', '1. The law presumes innocence until guilt is proved. 在罪状未证实前，法律假定被告无罪。 2. We presume that the factory has been fully engaged. 我们推测工厂的生产已经满负荷了。 3. That\'s the new assistant, I presume. 我想那就是新来的助理 4. I presume that this is your final answer. 我认为这就是你最后的答复。 5. May I presume to advise you? 我可以冒昧向你进一言吗？', '副词: presumedly 名词: presumer 过去式: presumed 过去分词: presumed 现在分词: presuming 第三人称单数: presumes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('barbarian', '[bɑːr\'beriən]', 'n.野蛮人 adj.野蛮的', '1. The barbarians conquered Rome. 野蛮人征服了罗马。 2. To the barbarian of the lower stage, a slave was valueless . 对于低级阶段的野蛮人来说，奴隶是没有价值的。 3. The barbarian defiled the church by use it as stable. 蛮夷人把教堂当作畜牲圈，使其受到玷污。 4. Rome went down before the barbarian invaders. 罗马被野蛮的侵略者所征服。', '名词: barbarianism');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('presidency', '[\'prezɪdənsi]', 'n.总统（总裁、主席等）的职位（或任期）', '1. He wants to run for the presidency. 他想竞选总统。 2. The tenure of the US Presidency is four years. 美国总统的任期是四年。', '名词复数: presidencies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('flux', '[flʌks]', 'n.流量；变迁；助熔剂 vt.使熔化；使泻；涨 vi.熔化', '1. There was no flux, no people and no business. 没有流量，没有人气，没有生意。 2. Variation in the ascertained flux depends on a number of factors. 已探知的流量的变更依赖许多因素。 3. The world is in continuous flux and is impermanent. 世界变迁不已，并非是常久不变的。 4. The neutrality flux must be used before soldering . 焊接时要求用中性助焊剂。 5. Melting behavior of silica flux in the converting process of high grade copper matte was investigated. 研究了高品位铜冰铜转炉吹炼石英熔剂熔化行为。', '过去式: fluxed 过去分词: fluxed 现在分词: fluxing 第三人称单数: fluxes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spring', '[sprɪŋ]', 'n.春天；春季；弹簧；弹力；跳；泉水；源头 v.跳；弹；快速站起；突然提出；触发捕捉器；(使)裂开；爆炸；释放；涌出；生长；出现；耸立；(风)开始吹', '1. Spring is here. 春天来了。 2. It can be quite windy there, especially in spring. 那里有时容易刮风,特别在春季。 3. When the box was opened, the spring jumped out. 盒子一打开，弹簧就绷出来了。 4. There is too much spring in this bed. 这张床太有弹性。 5. The cat crouched ready to spring. 那猫躬起背准备跳。', '过去式: sprang/sprung 过去分词: sprung 现在分词: springing 第三人称单数: springs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reiterate', '[ri\'ɪtəreɪt]', 'vt.重申', '1. The captain reiterated the command to us. 上尉对我们重申了那项命令。 2. We reiterate our determination to combat terrorism. 我们重申打击恐怖主义的决心。 3. I must reiterate that our position on this issue is very clear. 我必须重申我们对这一项议题的立场很清楚。', '形容词: reiterative 副词: reiteratively 名词: reiteration 过去式: reiterated 过去分词: reiterated 现在分词: reiterating 第三人称单数: reiterates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elusive', '[i\'luːsɪv]', 'adj.难懂的；难捉摸的；难找的；逃避的', '1. Number is a crucial but elusive concept in English teaching and learning. 数是英语教学中的一个关键而又难以捉摸的概念。 2. The Abominable Snowman who haunts the imagination of climbers in the Himalayas is hardly more elusive. 常使喜马拉雅山的攀登者浮想联翩的雪人也不比此更难以捉摸。 3. Men like to pursue an elusive woman, like a cake of wet soap in a bathtub- even men who hate bath. 男人们喜欢追逐那些象浴缸里的湿肥皂般难以捉摸的女人，即使是讨厌洗澡的男人也无不如此。 4. He spent a year prospecting for the elusive metal. 他花了一年的功夫去勘探那种很难到手的金属。', '副词: elusively 名词: elusiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('roll', '[roʊl]', 'n.卷；滚动；名单；压路机；颤音；圆形物，面包卷 v.摇摆；滚；绕；转动；展开', '1. Love comes quick and passes away quick too. Only the pork roll will go on. 爱情来得快去得也快,只有猪肉卷才是永恒的。 2. The desk calculator use a roll of paper. 这台台式计算机使用卷纸。 3. A ball can roll smoothly on a plane. 球可以在水平面上流畅地滚动。 4. Merlin tried different ways to make himself roll. 莫林试了很多不同的方式，想让自己滚动起来。 5. The ship was rolling heavily to and fro. 那船晃来晃去很不平稳。', '过去式: rolled 过去分词: rolled 现在分词: rolling 第三人称单数: rolls');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('purple', '[\'pɜːrpl]', 'adj.紫色的；辞藻华丽的 n.紫色；皇室', '1. The plant has a brilliant purple floweret. 那棵植物开着鲜艳的小紫花。 2. That girl likes to wear purple dresses. 那个女孩喜欢穿紫色的衣服。 3. He used to write purple prose. 他过去常写绚丽矫饰的散文。 4. His face turned purple with rage. 他气得脸色发紫。', '过去式: purpled 过去分词: purpled 现在分词: purpling 第三人称单数: purples');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gospel', '[\'ɡɑːspl]', 'n.新约圣经四福书之一；福音；真理', '1. The man was preaching the Gospel. 此人在传布福音。 2. Today there is another gospel being preached. 当今世代，所传讲的福音已是另一个福音。 3. We took the teacher\'s words as gospel. 我们把老师的话当作真理。 4. Then Paul re-iterates the great facts of the Gospel once more. 最后，保罗再次重申福音的伟大真理。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('immutable', '[ɪ\'mjuːtəbl]', 'adj.不可变的；不变的', '1. If the data is immutable, it may be practical to allow it to be de-normalized. 假如数据是不可变的，那么允许它不规格化是很实际的。 2. In summary, data that is distributed must be both immutable and stable. 总之，分布式的数据就必须是不可变的，稳定的。 3. The permanent and the immutable are persistent. 永恒不变的事物依然存在。 4. If the data is immutable, it may be practical to allow it to be de-normalized. 假如数据是不可变的，那么允许它不规格化是很实际的。', '副词: immutably 名词: immutability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('volcano', '[vɑːl\'keɪnoʊ]', 'n.火山', '1. Vesuvius is an active volcano. 维苏威山是一座活火山。 2. The eruption of volcano makes many people lose their lives. 火山的爆发使许多人丧失了生命。 3. That volcano cast forth lots of lava and ashes. 那火山喷了出大量熔岩和灰烬。 4. The erupting volcano was an awe-inspiring sight. 火山爆发是使人畏惧的景象。', '名词复数: volcanoes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('condemn', '[kən\'dem]', 'vt.谴责；判刑', '1. We must not condemn her on pure supposition. 我们不能单凭猜测就谴责她。 2. We condemn all sorts of slanders. 我们谴责一切诽谤中伤的言论。 3. Most people are willing to condemn violence. 大部分的人极力谴责暴力。 4. The criminal was condemned to death. 这个罪犯被判死刑。', '形容词: condemnable 名词: condemner 过去式: condemned 过去分词: condemned 现在分词: condemning 第三人称单数: condemns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('file', '[faɪl]', 'n.档案；卷宗；文件；锉刀，指甲锉 vt.把 ... 归档；提出(申请书、议案等)', '1. Put this letter in the main file. 把这封信放在主要文件夹中。 2. Would you please take a seat while I look into our file? 你先坐一下,我给你查一下我们的卷宗? 3. Put this letter in the main file. 把这封信放在主要文件夹中。 4. Please file those letters. 请把这些信件存档。', '过去式: filed 过去分词: filed 现在分词: filing 第三人称单数: files');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('jellyfish', '[\'dʒelifɪʃ]', 'n.水母；海蜇；意志薄弱的人', '1. A large jellyfish glides past you. 一只巨大的水母滑过你的身边。 2. Please don\'t talk me into eating this jellyfish. 不要说服我去吃海蜇。 3. Her husband is a perfect jellyfish. 她丈夫是个典型的优柔寡断的人。', '名词复数: jellyfish');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('debtor', '[\'detər]', 'n.借方；债务人', '1. In this transaction the lender is essentially lending more money to its debtor. 在这种情况下，贷方会把更多的钱借给借方。 2. The debtor and creditor must sign a document drawn up in accordance with government regulations. 借方和贷方必须签定一份依据政府规章草拟的文件。 3. Debt was secured on the debtor\'s person. 债务应由债务人本人兑现。 4. The guarantor shall be someone other than the debtor of the bill. 保证人由汇票债务人以外的他人担当。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('essay', '[\'eseɪ]', 'n.论文；短评；散文；试图 vt.尝试', '1. This essay is admirable in all respects. 这篇文章在各方面都很值得欣赏。 2. I had turn over my essay to the professor. 我已经把论文交给教授了。 3. This essay represents a considerable improvement on your recent work. 这篇论文说明你最近的工作取得了相当大的改进。 4. The teacher geve an essay on his composition. 老师给他的作文做了一个短评。 5. He essayed to speak but was told to be quiet. 他试图发言,但主席让他不要讲话。', '名词: essayer 过去式: essayed 过去分词: essayed 现在分词: essaying 第三人称单数: essays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perishable', '[\'perɪʃəbl]', 'adj.易腐烂的；会枯萎的；会死的 （复数）perishables:易腐烂的东西（尤指食物）.', '1. Perishable goods are piling up at the docks. 码头上易腐烂的货物堆积如山。 2. Unlike perishable agricultural products, oil can be stored in the ground. 不同于易腐烂的农产品，石油可以长期埋在地下。', '副词: perishably 名词: perishability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relax', '[rɪ\'læks]', 'v.休息；放松；使 ... 放松；放宽', '1. I just want to sit down and relax. 我只想坐下休息会。 2. I felt my shoulders relax a little. 我觉得我的肩膀放松了好多。 3. His muscles relaxed. 他的肌肉松弛了。 4. A good massage will relax your tired muscles. 舒服的按摩会让你疲惫的肌肉放松。', '形容词: relaxable 过去式: relaxed 过去分词: relaxed 现在分词: relaxing 第三人称单数: relaxes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prospect', '[\'prɑːspekt]', 'n.希望；前景；景色 v.勘探；寻找', '1. A rich harvest is in prospect. 丰收在望。 2. I see little prospect of an improvement in his condition. 我看他的情况没有什么改进的希望。 3. What do you think about the marketing prospect? 你觉得市场前景怎么样? 4. The prospect from the balcony was breathtaking. 从阳台上看去景色美极了。 5. They went there to prospect for gold . 他们去那儿勘探金矿。', '过去式: prospected 过去分词: prospected 现在分词: prospecting 第三人称单数: prospects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('partial', '[\'pɑːrʃl]', 'adj.不完全的；部分的；偏袒的；偏爱的', '1. around three 2. The research project was only a partial success. 那个研究课题只取得部分成功。 3. You will receive some partial credit even you don\'t finish it. 如果你没作完的话,你还是可以得到部分的分数。 4. His partial attitude called forth a lot of criticism. 他的偏袒态度招致了不少批评。', '名词: partialness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('remedy', '[\'remədi]', 'n.治疗法；药物；补救 vt.治疗；补救；矫正', '1. Warmth is the best remedy for colds. 热疗是治感冒的最好方法。 2. I can offer you a sure remedy. 我可以给你提供一个有效的疗法。 3. The remedy he purchased failed to work. 他买的药并不灵验。 4. The mistake is beyond remedy. 这个错误是无法补救的。 5. Aspirin may remedy a headache. 阿斯匹林可治头痛。', '名词复数: remedies 过去式: remedied 过去分词: remedied 现在分词: remedying 第三人称单数: remedies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('degrade', '[dɪ\'ɡreɪd]', 'v.降格；使屈辱；贬低；退化；降解', '1. You should not degrade yourself by telling such a lie. 你不该说那样的谎话降低自己的人格。 2. I felt degraded by having to ask for money. 不得不向别人要钱,我感到有失尊严。 3. No one can degrade us except ourselves. 除了我们自己，没有人能贬低我们。 4. For some reason our balancing reflexes degrade with age. 我们的平衡反射，由于某种原因，随着年龄的增长而退化。', '名词: degrader 过去式: degraded 过去分词: degraded 现在分词: degrading 第三人称单数: degrades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ineligible', '[ɪn\'elɪdʒəbl]', 'adj.无被选任资格的；不适任的；不适当的 n.无被选任资格的人；不合录用资格的人', '1. A foreign-born citizen is ineligible for the Presidency. 外籍公民没有资格任总统。 2. Any person under the age of 18 is ineligible for benefit. 未满18岁者无资格领取补助金。', '副词: ineligibly 名词: ineligibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skimpy', '[\'skɪmpi]', 'adj.(衣服等)尺寸小的；不足的；缺乏的；吝啬的', '1. I don\'t like those skimpy trousers. 我不喜欢这种小里小气的裤子。 2. They provided only skimpy details. 他们提供的细节不充分。 3. Her knowledge of art was skimpy. 她缺乏艺术方面的知识。', '副词: skimpily 比较级: skimpier 最高级: skimpiest 名词: skimpiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revolt', '[rɪ\'voʊlt]', 'n.叛乱；反抗；反感 v.叛乱；起反感', '1. The revolt was suppressed in a matter of hours. 叛乱在几小时之内就镇压下去了。 2. All North Africa would flame into revolt. 整个北非将激起反抗。 3. Her mere experience and the free out-of-door life of country caused her nature to revolt at such confinement. 她那简单的经验和自由自在的乡村户外生活，使她对这个窒息的地方起了反感。 4. The peasants revolted against their oppressors. 农民们起义反抗他们的压迫者。', '名词: revolter 过去式: revolted 过去分词: revolted 现在分词: revolting 第三人称单数: revolts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shuttle', '[\'ʃʌtl]', 'n.梭子；穿梭；往返移动之物；航天飞机 v.往返运送；穿梭移动', '1. The shuttle flies back and forth on the loom. 织布机上梭子来回飞动。 2. He refined the whole art of shuttle diplomacy. 他把穿梭外交艺术提高到炉火纯青的地步。 3. There is a shuttle service between the city center and the air station. 在市中心和飞机场之间有往返的穿梭运行班车。 4. The U.S. made the first space shuttle in the world. 美国制造了世界上第一架航天飞机。 5. We shuttled the passengers to the city center by helicopter. 我们来来回回地用直升机把旅客运送到市中心。', '名词: shuttler 过去式: shuttled 过去分词: shuttled 现在分词: shuttling 第三人称单数: shuttles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pretension', '[prɪ\'tenʃn]', 'n.声称；自命；要求；自负；狂妄；炫耀', '1. His social pretensions make him appear ridiculous. 他冒充上流社会人士而出尽洋相。 2. He has no pretensions to being an expert on the subject. 他并不以这方面专家自居。 3. Readers may find the pretension and arrogance of her style irritating. 读者可以感觉到她文章中的狂妄自负令人反感。 4. The play mocks the pretensions of the new middle class. 这出戏讽刺了新中产阶级的装模作样。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ascertain', '[ˌæsər\'teɪn]', 'vt.确定；查明；探知', '1. I ascertain that he was murdered. 我确定他是被谋杀的。 2. I ascertained the disease to be diphtheria. 我确定该病为白喉。 3. The detective was trying to ascertain exactly who was at the party. 这个侦探试图查明都有谁参加了聚会。 4. I\'m going to ascertain the truth. 我要查明真相。', '形容词: ascertainable 副词: ascertainably 名词: ascertainableness 过去式: ascertained 过去分词: ascertained 现在分词: ascertaining 第三人称单数: ascertains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hinterland', '[\'hɪntərlænd]', 'n.内陆地区；内地；腹地', '1. A century ago, eastern Germany was an agricultural hinterland. 一个世纪前, 德国东部是个农业的内陆地区。 2. Circuses in the hinterland were hilarious. 内地的马戏团非常热闹。 3. Her shows in border areas and the hinterland had a big influence. 她在边疆和内地演出颇具影响。 4. However, Dunhuang is located in the hinterland of the great desert. 然而，敦煌处在大漠的腹地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stout', '[staʊt]', 'adj.强壮的；肥胖的；牢固的；坚定的 n.烈啤酒', '1. Hope is a slender reed for a stout man to lean on. 希望是壮汉依靠的一根纤细的芦苇。 2. The stout old man waddled across the road. 那粗壮的老人摇摇摆摆地穿过大路。 3. He became stout as he grew older. 随着年龄的增长，他发胖了。 4. The balloon was tied down to a stout stake. 气球被拴在一个结实的木桩上。 5. This stout has a slight chocolate flavor. 这种烈性啤酒有点巧克力的味道。', '形容词: stoutish 副词: stoutly 比较级: stouter 最高级: stoutest 名词: stoutness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('thermometer', '[θər\'mɑːmɪtər]', 'n.温度计', '1. The thermometer reads 27 degrees. 温度计的读数是27度。 2. The thermometer fell to zero lastnight. 昨夜温度计显示气温下降到零度。 3. The readings on my thermometer last month were well above the average. 我的温度计上个月的读数远远超过平均温度。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mammals', '[\'mæml]', 'n.哺乳动物 名词mammal的复数形式.', '1. Man and most other mammals are viviparous. 人和其他大多数哺乳动物都是胎生的。 2. Among mammals whales have the greatest mass. 哺乳动物中以鲸鱼最大。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dioxide', '[daɪ\'ɑːksaɪd]', 'n.二氧化物', '1. The carbon14 atoms oxidize to carbon dioxide which gets blown about and mixed up with lower atmosphere. 碳14原子氧化生成二氧化碳，向四周散去并与低空的大气混合。 2. Soft drinks contain carbon dioxide. 软饮料中含有二氧化碳。 3. Plants can absorb carbon dioxide and release oxygen. 植物可以吸收二氧化碳释放氧气。 4. Acid rain is caused by sculptures dioxide spewed from factories and power plants. 酸雨的形成是从工厂和发电厂被排放的二氧化物引起。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circulation', '[ˌsɜːrkjə\'leɪʃn]', 'n.流通；循环；发行量；消息传播', '1. The old coins have been withdrawn from circulation. 旧硬币已经收回不再流通了。 2. The coins were taken out of circulation. 这种硬币已停止流通。 3. Harvey discovered the circulation of the blood. 哈唯发现了血液循环。 4. The newspaper\'s circulation has trebled since last year. 去年以来该报的发行量已增加到原来的三倍。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('begrudge', '[bɪ\'ɡrʌdʒ]', 'v.嫉妒；羡慕；吝啬', '1. Nobody begrudges you your success. 没有人忌妒你的成功。 2. We should not begrudge our neighbour\'s richness. 我们不应该嫉妒邻人的富有。 3. I begrudge him his good fortune. 我羡慕他的运气好. 4. We don\'t begrudge your going to Italy. 我们并不羡慕你到意大利去。', '副词: begrudgingly 名词: begrudger 过去式: begrudged 过去分词: begrudged 现在分词: begrudging 第三人称单数: begrudges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('mosaic', '[moʊ\'zeɪɪk]', 'n.马赛克；镶嵌图案 v.镶嵌；用马赛克装饰 adj.【大写】摩西的', '1. I stared for hours at the elaborate pattern in the mosaic. 我对着马赛克上精密的图案注视了好几个小时。 2. Archaeologists have worked for years to piece together the huge mosaic. 考古学家经年累月拼组这幅巨大的马赛克。 3. It\'s a rich mosaic of meadows, rivers and woods. 这是一幅由草地，河流，树木组成的五光十色的镶嵌画。 4. The sky this morning was a mosaic of blue and white. 今天早上的天空是幅蓝白相间的画面。 5. Mosaic a design on a rosewood box. 将一个图案嵌入红木盒子上。', '名词: mosaicist 过去式: mosaicked 过去分词: mosaicked 现在分词: mosaicking 第三人称单数: mosaics');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('generously', '[\'dʒenərəsli]', 'adv.宽大地；慷慨地', '1. She has contributed generously to the Red Cross. 她曾慷慨地向红十字会捐款。 2. They generously accorded me permission to use their library. 他们慷慨地允许我使用他们的图书馆。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oblivious', '[ə\'blɪviəs]', 'adj.没注意到；健忘的', '1. I was oblivious of my surroundings. 我没有注意到周围的事物。 2. He sat there reading the book, oblivious of the people nearby. 他坐在那里看书,没注意到附近的人们。 3. I am oblivious to what was happening. 我对发生的事情没有记忆了。 4. He was oblivious of his promise. 他忘记了他的诺言。', '副词: obliviously 名词: obliviousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fundamental', '[ˌfʌndə\'mentl]', 'adj.基本的；根本的；重要的 n.基础；基本原理', '1. For something fundamental has changed in Venezuela. 因为在委内瑞拉，有一些基本的东西已经改变了。 2. Trial by the jury is a fundamental right. 有陪审团陪同审判是一项基本的权利。 3. From the outset, it had two fundamental flaws. 从一开始，这一合作就有两个根本的缺陷。 4. The fundamental ones are embodied in the Party Constitution. 党章是最根本的党规党法。 5. Primary is about fundamental play. 原始与基础游戏有关。', '副词: fundamentally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abuse', '[ə\'bjuːs]', 'n.滥用；恶习 vt.滥用；辱骂；虐待', '1. The government has set up a working party to look into the problem of drug abuse. 政府已成立工作组调查滥用毒品问题。 2. His political reputation was tainted by his abuse of the power. 他因滥用职权而破坏了政治声誉。 3. He greeted me with a stream of abuse. 他见到我就连声辱骂。 4. It\'s easy to abuse one\'s power. 人容易滥用权力。', '名词: abuser 过去式: abused 过去分词: abused 现在分词: abusing 第三人称单数: abuses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('opaque', '[oʊ\'peɪk]', 'adj.不透明的；难懂的', '1. This is an opaque cup. 这是一个不透明的杯子。 2. The window is made of opaque glass. 这扇窗是用不透明的玻璃做的。 3. The report was written in long, opaque sentences. 报告中的句子又长又难懂。 4. Their intentions remained opaque. 他们的意图仍然令人费解。', '副词: opaquely 名词: opaqueness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('blast', '[blæst]', 'n.爆炸；巨响；一阵(强风)；严厉的批评；<美俚>愉快的经历 v.爆破；摧毁；发出巨响；用力撞击；批评', '1. 27 school children were injured in the blast. 27名学龄儿童在爆炸中受了伤。 2. A blast of the trumpet gave her a start. 突然发出的喇叭声吓了她一跳。 3. A blast of wind blew my hat off. 一阵风吹走了我的帽子。 4. The press responded to his remarks with a blast of criticism. 新闻界以严厉的批评回应了他的言论。 5. A massive car bomb blasted the police headquarters. 一个巨大的汽车炸弹在警局总部爆炸。', '名词: blaster 过去式: blasted 过去分词: blasted 现在分词: blasting 第三人称单数: blasts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cynical', '[\'sɪnɪkl]', 'adj.愤世嫉俗的；悲观的；恶意的', '1. She is getting more cynical about life. 她变得对生活更加愤世嫉俗。 2. His cynical attitude gave us a surprise. 他那愤世嫉俗的态度让我们惊奇。 3. With that cynical outlook, he doesn\'t trust anyone. 抱着那种愤世嫉俗的观点, 他不相信任何人。 4. The story depicts the hero as a cynical opportunist. 小说把主人公描写成一个悲观的机会主义者。', '副词: cynically 名词: cynicalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('botany', '[\'bɑːtəni]', 'n.植物学；植物', '1. To what degree are you interested in botany? 你对植物学的兴趣达到什么程度？ 2. In learning botany, I understand much about nature. 学习植物学使我对大自然了解了许多。 3. Botany deals with the study of plants. 植物学论述植物的研究。 4. He taught Irene botany and natural history. 他教绮瑞娜认识植物和学习自然史。', '名词复数: botanies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('torrent', '[\'tɔːrənt]', 'n.激流；山洪；(谩骂、质问等的)连发，爆发', '1. The river was a torrent after the storm. 暴风雨过后，河水成了激流。 2. The torrent scoured a gully down the hillside. 那激流顺山坡而下冲出一条水沟。 3. A torrent of water poured down the mountain. 洪水从山上奔流而下。 4. She attacked him with a torrent of abuse. 她用连珠炮似的谩骂来攻击他。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('awful', '[\'ɔːfl]', 'adj.糟糕的；可怕的；充满敬畏的；难受的 adv.极其', '1. It would be awful if he found out the truth. 如果他发现了真相，那就糟了。 2. I left Harvard with no real awareness of the awful inequities in the world. 当我离开哈佛时,我并没真正有意识到这个世界存在着可怕的不平等现象。 3. He seemed to be very awful while serving the famous actress. 他在招待那位著名的女演员时,看上去非常的敬畏。 4. I feel awful about not inviting her. 没有邀请她,我感到很内疚。 5. These weeks is an awful long time to wait. 这几个星期真的是一段极其漫长的等待时间啊。', '副词: awfully 名词: awfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fetter', '[\'fetər]', 'v.为 ... 上脚镣；束缚；限制 n.脚镣；桎梏', '1. He was fettered by his family and could not travel any longer. 他被家庭束缚，不能再到处去旅游了。 2. You may imprison my body, but you could not fetter my mind. 你可以禁锢我的身体，却束缚不了我的心灵。 3. This does not mean that we wish to fetter the trade union movement. 这并不意味着我们想限制工会运动。 4. The prisoner was put into the jail with fetters. 这个犯人被戴上脚镣投进了监狱。', '过去式: fettered 过去分词: fettered 现在分词: fettering 第三人称单数: fetters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('desperate', '[\'despərət]', 'adj.绝望的；不顾一切的；极其想要的', '1. The situation is desperate. 情况令人感到绝。 2. I had no money left and was desperate. 我一点钱都没有了,简直绝望了。 3. They made a desperate plea for help. 他们不顾一切地恳求帮助。 4. His failure made him desperate. 他因失败而铤而走险。', '副词: desperately 名词: desperateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gemstone', '[\'dʒemstəʊn]', 'n.经雕琢的宝石 =gem.', '1. Aquamarine is a fascinatingly beautiful gemstone. 海蓝宝石是很有趣且迷人的宝石。 2. We mainly do pearl and gemstone jewelry. 我们主要是做珍珠和宝石首饰。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('revive', '[rɪ\'vaɪv]', 'vt.使重生；恢复精神；唤醒 vi.复生', '1. We tried to revive him but without avail. 我们试图使他苏醒,但没有成功。 2. The flowers will revive in water. 这些花在水中会再活。 3. Revive your spirit and add shine to your hair. 重振你的精神，给你的头发增添光亮。 4. We need something to revive our hopes. 我们需要一些什么东西来重新恢复我们的希望。', '形容词: revivable 名词: reviver 过去式: revived 过去分词: revived 现在分词: reviving 第三人称单数: revives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('burning', '[\'bɜːrnɪŋ]', 'adj.燃烧的；热烈的；紧急的 n.燃烧 动词burn的现在分词.', '1. Passengers suffocated in the burning aircraft. 乘客在燃烧的飞机中窒息死亡。 2. Teachers are often compared to burning candles. 人们总是把老师比喻为燃烧的蜡烛。 3. Researchers found that women are overcome by a burning desire to share gossip as soon as they hear it. 研究人员发现，女人被一听到流言就迫不及待地想要分享的强烈欲望所征服。 4. These days, crimes against humanities are burning issue. 近日，反人道主义的犯罪是一个热点话题。 5. The farmers compressed straw into blocks for burning. 农民们将干草压成块用来烧火。', '副词: burningly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unique', '[ju\'niːk]', 'adj.独特的；独一无二的；稀罕的', '1. He occupies a unique place in English literature. 他在英国文学中占有独特的地位。 2. The elephant\'s trunk is a unique form of appendage. 象的鼻子是一种独特的附肢。 3. It\'s a unique work of art. 这是独一无二的艺术作品。 4. The custom is unique to the region. 这种风俗是这一地区特有的。', '副词: uniquely 名词: uniqueness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('avarice', '[\'ævərɪs]', 'n.贪财；贪婪', '1. The old man shows great avarice for money. 这个老头视钱如命。 2. Avarice drove him into theft. 贪婪驱使他偷窃。 3. Avarice is the root of all evils. 贪婪是万恶之源。 4. He fell victim to his own avarice. 他由于贪婪而自食其果。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pasture', '[\'pæstʃər]', 'n.牧场；草原 vi.吃草 vt.放牧', '1. The land was used chiefly for pasture. 这土地多半用作牧场。 2. We have put our cattle out to pasture. 我们已经把牛放到牧场上吃草去了。 3. Cows are grazing in the pasture. 牛正在草原吃草。 4. Draping the skin over his shoulders, he went to the pasture to wait for the lion. 把羊皮披在身上后，猎人到草原上去等狮子。 5. There we saw herds of cows grazing on the pasture. 我们在那里看到一群群的牛在草地上吃草。 6. Cows are left to graze in the pasture. 奶牛都是留给放牧在牧场。', '形容词: pasturable 名词: pasturer 过去式: pastured 过去分词: pastured 现在分词: pasturing 第三人称单数: pastures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decimal', '[\'desɪml]', 'adj.小数的；十进位的 n.小数', '1. The first two figures after the decimal point indicate tenths and hundredths respectively. 小数点后的头两位数分别表示十分位和百分位。 2. Most countries have a decimal currency. 大多数国家使用十进制货币。 3. There were only decimal math problem on the quiz. 测验中只有十进位的数学题。 4. Britain converted to a decimal currency system in 1971. 英国于1971年改行十进制货币体系。 5. 0.3 is a decimal. 0.', '副词: decimally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('absorb', '[əb\'sɔːrb]', 'vt.吸收；吸引 ... 的注意；吞并；承受', '1. Dry sand absorbs water. 干沙吸收水份。 2. Did you absorb everything the professor said? 教授说的你全部理解了吗? 3. His business absorbs him. 他的业务使他全神贯注。 4. Large nations shouldn\'t absorb smaller ones. 大国不应当吞并小国。', '形容词: absorbable 副词: absorbingly 名词: absorbability 过去式: absorbed 过去分词: absorbed 现在分词: absorbing 第三人称单数: absorbs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ethics', '[\'eθɪks]', 'n.道德规范；道德标准；伦理学', '1. The ethics of his decision are doubtful. 他的这一决定是否合乎道德规范值得怀疑。 2. Medical ethics forbid a doctor to have a love affair with a patient. 行医道德有规定,禁止医生与病人谈恋爱。 3. Lee carries over his business ethics into his personal relationships. 李把他在生意中的道德标准运用到私人关系中去。 4. He began to question the ethics of his position. 他开始对他的立场是否符合道德准则提出质疑。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('addicted', '[ə\'dɪktɪd]', 'adj.沉溺于的；有毒瘾的', '1. He\'s finally off (ie is no longer addicted to) drugs. 他终於戒了毒了。 2. He\'s hooked on (ie addicted to) speed. 他使用安非他明已成瘾。 3. Smokers who inhale are likely to become addicted to nicotine. 吸烟的人容易对尼古丁上瘾。 4. He is addicted to alcohol. 他嗜好喝酒。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ordeal', '[ɔːr\'diːl]', 'n.严酷的考验；痛苦的经验；神裁法', '1. Through this ordeal Heng lay stiff and silent. 在这个严酷的考验中，恒一直僵硬地躺着，默不作声。 2. Once there we saw that the ordeal must have been great. 从前我们觉得严酷的考验一定是很伟大的。 3. I\'d hate to go through such a terrible ordeal again. 我不想再受这种痛苦的经验。 4. Excessive choices quickly stop being a benefit and become an ordeal. 过多的选择很快就丧失了它的优势，而成为一种痛苦的经验。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('corroborate', '[kə\'rɑːbəreɪt]', 'v.确证；证实', '1. There\'s nothing to corroborate your story. 无任何东西可以确证你的话。 2. Some observations do seem to corroborate the idea. 而某些观察所得似乎也佐证了这种想法。 3. Experiments have corroborated her predictions. 实验证实了她的预言。 4. His friend corroborated his guilt. 他的朋友证实了他的犯罪。', '形容词: corroborative 名词: corroboration 过去式: corroborated 过去分词: corroborated 现在分词: corroborating 第三人称单数: corroborates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('aware', '[ə\'wer]', 'adj.知道的；意识到的', '1. If you were aware of all that, you would change your mind. 如果你知道了那一切,你会改变主意的。 2. Then he became aware that they were regarding him with interest. 这时,他意识到他们都在饶有兴趣地看着他。', '名词: awareness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shuffle', '[\'ʃʌfl]', 'v.拖曳；搅乱；推诿；洗牌；移来移去 n.洗牌；搅乱；拖着脚走；搪塞', '1. The prisoners shuffled along the corridor and into their cells. 囚犯们沿着走廊拖着脚步进入牢房。 2. Don\'t shuffle the papers together. 不要把文件混在一起。 3. Don\'t shuffle, give me a clear answer. 别支支吾吾，给我一个明确的答复。 4. He tries to shuffle his work off onto others. 他想把工作推给别人。 5. Give the cards a good shuffle. 把牌好好洗一洗。', '名词: shuffler 过去式: shuffled 过去分词: shuffled 现在分词: shuffling 第三人称单数: shuffles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('photography', '[fə\'tɑːɡrəfi]', 'n.摄影', '1. Photography is her favourite pastime. 摄影是她喜爱的消遣。 2. He has a passion for photography. 他对摄影有强烈的爱好。 3. The contrast of light and shade is important in photography. 在摄影艺术中明暗的反差是很重要的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('concurrence', '[kən\'kɜːrəns]', 'n.赞同；意见一致；同时发生', '1. With your concurrence, I will confirm the arrangement. 你若同意 2. There is a concurrence of opinion between them. 他们的想法一致。 3. Our concurrence is the precondition for a breakthrough. 取得突破的前提是我们的意见一致. 4. This concurrence avoids the need to parallelize at the level of each clinic location or patient. 这种并发可以避免在每一次门诊所在的位置或涉及的患者这个层次上实现并行化。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cultivate', '[\'kʌltɪveɪt]', 'vt.栽培；耕作；培养；陶冶；结交(朋友)', '1. He was granted many privileges to cultivate crops. 他被给予许多特权来培育农作物。 2. They moved to the country to cultivate the soil . 他们搬到乡下去种地。 3. The people cultivate mainly rice and beans. 这里的人们主要种植稻子和豆类。 4. Father tries to cultivate my love for art. 父亲企图培养我对艺术的爱好。', '形容词: cultivatable 过去式: cultivated 过去分词: cultivated 现在分词: cultivating 第三人称单数: cultivates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('chirp', '[tʃɜːrp]', 'v.吱喳而鸣；轻松愉快地说 n.喳喳声；唧唧声', '1. At night the crickets chirp in the woods. 夜里蟋蟀在林中唧唧地叫。 2. Birds had begun to chirp among the trees. 鸟儿们已经开始在树林里叽叽喳喳地叫了。 3. I was awakened by the chirps of the birds this morning. 今天早晨我被鸟叫声唤醒。 4. A cricket an inch long has a chirp that is audible for nearly a mile. 一英寸长的蟋蟀发出的唧唧声在将近一英里远的地方都能听见。', '过去式: chirped 过去分词: chirped 现在分词: chirping 第三人称单数: chirps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('smash', '[smæʃ]', 'v.打碎；粉碎；猛撞 n.破碎；撞击；轰动的演出；[网球]高压扣球 adj.极为成功的', '1. The bottle slipped and smashed to pieces on the floor. 瓶子滑在地上,摔成碎片。 2. We shall thoroughly smash the scheme of the enemy. 我们要彻底粉碎敌人的阴谋。 3. We must be ready at all times to smash the enemy\'s attacks. 我们必须随时准备粉碎敌人的进攻。 4. I lost my key and had to smash the window open. 我把钥匙弄丢了,只好把窗户撞开进屋了。 5. The teapot fell with an awful smash. 茶壶掉下来摔得粉碎。 6. The play had its smash premiere. 那出戏首场演出引起了极大的轰动。', '名词: smasher 过去式: smashed 过去分词: smashed 现在分词: smashing 第三人称单数: smashes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dive', '[daɪv]', 'n.潜水；跳水 vi.跳水；俯冲；潜心钻研', '1. Our dive is a part of this expedition. 我们这次潜水活动就是属于这个远航的一部分。 2. What a beautiful dive! 多么优美的跳水！ 3. He dived from the bridge and rescued the drowning child. 他从桥上跳入水中，救起溺水的孩子。 4. The eagle dived down on the rabbit. 那只鹰向兔子猛扑下来。', '过去式: dived/dove 过去分词: dived 现在分词: diving 第三人称单数: dives');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shortly', '[\'ʃɔːrtli]', 'adv.立刻；马上', '1. Know that these aches and pains are just blockages and that they will be moved shortly. 了解这些伤痛不过只是沮滞并且将立刻被移除。 2. And it\'s hardly a coincidence that shortly after Usmanov hires a big shot PR firm these kinds of pieces begin to appear in the papers. 当乌斯马诺夫刚刚雇用了强悍的公关公司后，这类东西就立刻出现在报纸上，很难让人信服这只是一种巧合。 3. I hope to announce the winner shortly. 我希望马上宣布胜利者的名字。 4. I shall therefore be going to the bank shortly to complete these formalities so that there is no further delay in releasing the documents and consignment. 我因此将打算马上去银行来完成这些手续以便在让渡货物和文件的过程中别再耽误了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('commemorate', '[kə\'meməreɪt]', 'vt.纪念', '1. A monument was built to commemorate the victory. 为了纪念胜利，建造了一座纪念碑。 2. Christmas commemorates the birth of Christ. 圣诞节是为了纪念耶酥的诞生。 3. They reared a monument to commemorate the great musician. 他们建立起一座纪念碑，纪念这位伟大的音乐家。 4. We celebrate this day to commemorate the brave soldiers. 我们庆祝这天，以纪念英勇的士兵。', '名词: commemorator 过去式: commemorated 过去分词: commemorated 现在分词: commemorating 第三人称单数: commemorates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pound', '[paʊnd]', 'n.磅；英镑 n.（汽车）扣押所；宠物收留所 vt.捣碎；敲打；连续猛击 vi.咚咚地走；怦怦地响', '1. I lost several pounds last month. 我上个月瘦了好几磅。 2. The shop is selling choice apple, so I buy 3 pound. 那商店在卖上选苹果,所以我买了三磅。 3. There is a 1 pound admission charge. 入场费为1英镑。 4. I paid him b pound , and he gave me 20 pence change. 我付了一英镑 5. Have you redeemed your car from the pound? 你有没有取回被扣的汽车? 6. The farmers pound rice in a mortar. 农民们在臼中舂米。 7. Do not pound up the stairs! 上楼梯不要跺脚！', '名词: pounder 名词复数: pound 过去式: pounded 过去分词: pounded 现在分词: pounding 第三人称单数: pounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('diplomat', '[\'dɪpləmæt]', 'n.外交官；通权达变之人', '1. They had to ransom the kidnapped diplomat. 他们不得不赎回被绑架的外交官。 2. In all the delicate negotiations, the diplomat never put a foot wrong. 在微妙的谈判中，这位外交家从未出过差错。 3. The diplomat solved the international problem by negotiating. 外交官通过谈判解决了那个国际问题。 4. You act as a diplomat and harmonizer between people with differing viewpoints. 在人们之间，你就应该像一个外交大使一样，见人说人话，见鬼说鬼话。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('serenity', '[sə\'renəti]', 'n.宁静；沉着', '1. They did not know which was most worthy of admiration, his pallor or his serenity. 我们不知道究竟哪一样最使人肃然起敬，是他面色的惨白呢，还是他神宇的宁静。 2. I enjoyed the serenity and the peacefulness when I was in the church. 当我身处大教堂时赶到平和与宁静。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('previous', '[\'priːviəs]', 'adj.以前的；先于；在 ... 之前', '1. His previous attempts had been unsuccessful. 他以前的尝试没有成功。 2. It happened previous to his arrival there. 事件发生于他到那儿以前。 3. You must collect enough materials previous to your writing. 你在写作之前必须收集好足够的材料。', '副词: previously 名词: previousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('phenomenon', '[fə\'nɑːmɪnən]', 'n.现象；奇人；奇事', '1. Their so-called prosperity is only a temporary phenomenon. 但他们所谓的繁荣只是一个暂时的现象。 2. International terrorism is not just a recent phenomenon. 国际恐怖主义并不是近年才有的现象。 3. Magnetism is a natural phenomenon. 磁力是一种自然现象。 4. A child who could read at the age of one would indeed be a phenomenon. 一个一岁的孩子能阅读，会被认为是个神童。', '名词复数: phenomena');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crude', '[kruːd]', 'adj.天然的；未加工的；粗鲁的；粗糙的；简陋的 n.原油；天然的物质', '1. China is a country rich in crude oil. 中国是一个原油丰富的国家。 2. The price of crude oil has come down recently. 最近原油的价格已经下降了。 3. This crude glycerin is from pure virgin vegetable oil. 这是未加工的甘油，来自纯洁，原始的植物油。 4. It was crude of him to say that. 他那样说太粗鲁了。 5. In fact, a speciality crude is suitable only for bitumen production. 事实上，这种特性的原油只适宜于生产沥青。', '副词: crudely 比较级: cruder 最高级: crudest 名词: crudity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adorn', '[ə\'dɔːrn]', 'v.装饰；佩戴', '1. Some of Dem Bones open the big trunks and take out jewels and ropes of pearls and adorn themselves. 一些德国马克的骨头打开大箱子，并采取了珠宝和绳索的珍珠和装饰自己。 2. A shiny gold, rimless frame with brown, gradient lenses is wrapped in delicate gold rhinestones that adorn the temple. 闪亮的金色，棕色无框框架，梯度镜头是包裹微妙的金色人造钻石装饰眼镜脚。 3. She likes to adorn herself with jewels. 她喜欢佩戴珠宝。 4. Have the nearsighted patient of astigmatism, can you adorn invisible glasses? 患有散光的近视患者，能佩戴隐形眼镜吗？', '名词: adorner 过去式: adorned 过去分词: adorned 现在分词: adorning 第三人称单数: adorns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('heirship', '[\'eəˌʃɪp]', 'n.继承权', '1. Joint inheritanceor heirship of property. 共同继承财产的共同继承或共同继承权。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('energize', '[\'enərdʒaɪz]', 'v.使活跃；赋予能量；激励；使精力充沛', '1. To worry is often to energize needlessly. 忧虑往往是浪费精力。 2. If you can\'t energize others, you are not a leader. 如果你不能激发别人,你就不是一个好领导。 3. Energize the incoming power feeder. 接通所有输入电源。 4. Protein foods energize, some experts say. 有些专家说蛋白质食品给人们提供能量。', '名词: energizer 过去式: energized 过去分词: energized 现在分词: energizing 第三人称单数: energizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indefatigable', '[ˌɪndɪ\'fætɪɡəbl]', 'adj.不知疲倦的；不屈不挠的', '1. The indefatigable bell now sounded for the fourth time. 那不知疲倦的钟声如今敲第四遍了。 2. He was indefatigable in his lectures on the aesthetics of love. 在讲授关于爱情的美学时，他是不知疲倦的。 3. Encouraged by this discovery, Edmond determined to assist the indefatigable laborer. 在这个发现的鼓舞之下，爱德蒙决心要帮助那个不屈不挠的劳动者。', '副词: indefatigably 名词: indefatigability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pliable', '[\'plaɪəbl]', 'adj.易曲折的；柔软的；圆滑的', '1. These tubes are lightweight, soft and pliable. 这些管子重量轻，柔软易弯曲。', '副词: pliably 名词: pliability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('zone', '[zoʊn]', 'n.地域；地带；地区', '1. They are pulling their troops out of the battle zone. 他们正把部队调离战区。 2. They have declared their country a, nuclear-free zone. 他们宣布本国为无核区。 3. Most of China is in the temperate zone. 中国的大部分地区在温带。 4. Some people live in Torrid Zone. 有些人生活在热带。', '过去式: zoned 过去分词: zoned 现在分词: zoning 第三人称单数: zones');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('indictment', '[ɪn\'daɪtmənt]', 'n.起诉；控告；起诉状', '1. They quashed the indictment against the manager. 他们撤销了对经理的起诉。 2. Don\'t view it as an indictment of you as a person. 不要把它看成是对你本人的一次起诉。 3. Even threats of indictment didn\'t loosen the tongue of the balky witness. 即使威胁要控告他也不能使这一不肯合作的证人说出一个字来。 4. I do not know the method of drawing up an indictment against an whole people. 我不知道如何起草控告所有人的方法。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('element', '[\'elɪmənt]', 'n.要素；元素；（学科的）基本原则；(复数)恶劣天气；元件', '1. Justice is an important element of good government. 公正是仁政的要素. 2. Honesty, industry and kindness are elements of a good life. 诚实、勤劳和善良是幸福生活的要素。 3. Water is composed of the elements hydrogen and oxygen. 水是由氢元素和氧元素组成的。 4. You must understand the elements of mathematics before we can proceed further. 你必须先弄懂数学基础知识，我们才能进一步学习。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('retract', '[rɪ\'trækt]', 'v.缩回；收回；撤销', '1. The undercarriage on light aircraft does not always retract in flight. 轻型飞机飞行时起落架不一定缩回。 2. I decided to retract what I had said before. 我决定收回前面说过的话。 3. Sir Alex has added his backing and believes Franco should retract his comments. 弗格森爵士支持自己的助理，并且强调里斯本竞技俱乐部主席应该收回自己的控诉。 4. The accused refused to retract his statement. 那被告拒不撤销其供述。', '形容词: retractable 名词: retractability 过去式: retracted 过去分词: retracted 现在分词: retracting 第三人称单数: retracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('souvenir', '[ˌsuːvə\'nɪr]', 'n.纪念品', '1. Can you mail this souvenir to America for me? 您能帮我把这件纪念品邮到美国吗? 2. I bought this bag as a souvenir of my visit to London. 我买了这个袋子作为访问伦敦的纪念品。 3. My favorite souvenir is my key chain from China. 我最喜欢的纪念品是在中国买的钥匙链。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vocal', '[\'voʊkl]', 'adj.声音的；口头的；声乐的；直言不讳的 n.元音；声乐作品', '1. The tongue is one of the vocals. 舌头是发声器官之一。 2. In the present instance he took no notice of my abrupt vocal response. 在目前这个情况下，他不去注意我那突兀的口头回答。 3. I like instrumental music better than vocal music. 我喜欢器乐胜于声乐。 4. He has been very vocal in his criticism of the government\'s policy. 他对政府政策的批评一直是直言不讳。 5. I select the two artists who have the commeasurable from the multitudinous outstanding vocal music performing artists to analyze and compare. 然而，她们却在声乐作品演唱方面表现出了不尽相同的理解，并形成和确立了截然不同的个人演唱风格。', '副词: vocally 名词: vocalness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('legible', '[\'ledʒəbl]', 'adj.清晰的；易读的；可辨认的', '1. Then he sat down next to Voisin and began to write, carefully, without hurry, a thin legible hand. 他不慌不忙，认认真真地写下一串纤细而清晰的字迹。 2. It was also decided that the value would be indicated clearly in a readily legible manner and that certain tactile features would be included. 它也被决定价值会以不迟疑清晰的样子被清楚地指出而且特定的触觉特征会被包括在内。 3. Judicious use of white space and legible fonts is important so that these signposts remain clearly evident and distinct. 明智地使用空白的空间和易读的字体很重要，这样将使标志保持清晰独特。', '副词: legibly 名词: legibility');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('temperate', '[\'tempərət]', 'adj.温和的；适度的；有节制的', '1. I love the temperate climate here. 我喜欢这儿温和的气候。 2. It is rare for so temperate a man to get angry. 象他这样性情温和的人发脾气是很少见的。 3. And he is steeped through and through with profound yet temperate happiness. 所以完全沉浸于深深的而又适度的幸福之中。 4. He is a temperate man, and never drinks too much. 他是一个有节制的人，从不过量饮酒。', '副词: temperately 名词: temperateness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('trifling', '[\'traɪflɪŋ]', 'adj.微不足道的；轻浮的 动词trifle的现在分词形式.', '1. Don\'t bother about that trifling matter. 别为那件小事烦恼。 2. They knocked a clock down for a trifling sum. 他们以微不足道的价格拍卖掉一只钟。 3. He was a trifling worthless fellow, and as mean a man as ever wore a crown. 他是个轻浮无德的人，是历来最卑鄙的一个君主。 4. He was not very solid to others but there was a hope of his becoming less trifling. 他为人不很严肃,但他有可能变得不那么轻浮。', '副词: triflingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('assault', '[ə\'sɔːlt]', 'n.攻击；突袭；抨击 vt.袭击；突袭', '1. Trainee commandos are put through an exhausting assault course. 受训的突击队员要参加令人筋疲力尽的突击课程。 2. The court determined that the man was guilty of assault. 法庭裁定那个人犯了侵犯人身罪。 3. A deep, wide ditch, usually filled with water, typically surrounding a fortified medieval town, fortress, or castle as a protection against assault. 护城河一条深而宽的、通常有水沟环绕设防的中世纪城镇城堡或堡垒，用以抵抗外来袭击 4. The article was a vicious assault on Bell\'s integrity. 这篇文章是对贝尔完整性的恶劣抨击。 5. Six women have been sexually assaulted in the area recently. 最近这一带有六个女子遭受强奸猥亵。', '名词: assaulter 过去式: assaulted 过去分词: assaulted 现在分词: assaulting 第三人称单数: assaults');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('context', '[\'kɒntekst]', 'n.上下文；环境；背景', '1. It is usually easier to pick out the meaning of a phrase in a given context. 在特定的上下文中理解一个短语的含意往往要更容易些。 2. In the context of the present economic crisis it seems unwise to lower taxes. 鉴於当前的经济危机，降低税率似乎不妥。 3. This speech needs to be set in the context of Britain in the 1960s. 这篇演说需要放到20世纪60年代的英国这一背景之下来看待。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('novel', '[\'nɑːvl]', 'n.小说 adj.新奇的', '1. The novel is considered a brilliant performance. 这部小说被认为是出色的佳作。 2. I like reading novels in my spare time. 我喜欢闲暇时读小说。 3. This film is based on a novel by D.H.Lawrence. 这部影片是根据D. 4. It\'s a novel idea. 那是个异常的想法。', '副词: novelly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('applaud', '[ə\'plɔːd]', 'vi.拍手喝彩 vt.称赞；赞成；鼓掌', '1. He leaped to his feet and began to applaud. 他跳起来开始鼓掌。 2. Please don\'t applaud until everyone has performed. 请在每个人表演完毕后再鼓掌。 3. Should I applaud my husband or chastise him? 我是该称赞还是责罚我的丈夫呢？ 4. Before I begin to flame anything, I would like to applaud a few folks. 在我开始对任何事激动之前,我想称赞一些人。', '形容词: applaudable 副词: applaudably 名词: applauder 过去式: applauded 过去分词: applauded 现在分词: applauding 第三人称单数: applauds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('comply', '[kəm\'plaɪ]', 'vi.顺从；遵照；答应', '1. She was told to pay the fine, but refused to comply. 通知她交纳罚款，但她拒不服从。 2. He was willing to comply with my proposal. 他愿意顺从我的建议。 3. Everyone should comply with the law. 每个人都应该遵守法律。 4. Is it our duty to comply with his requests? 我们有义务满足他的要求吗?', '过去式: complied 过去分词: complied 现在分词: complying 第三人称单数: complies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('guilty', '[\'ɡɪlti]', 'adj.有罪的；内疚的', '1. The court found him guilty. 法官判他有罪。 2. The man was proved guilty of murder. 这个男子被证实犯了杀人罪。 3. A man is accounted innocent until he is proven guilty. 一个人未被证明有罪前，被视为是清白的。 4. His answer evidenced a guilty conscience. 他的回答证明他良心有愧。', '副词: guiltily 比较级: guiltier 最高级: guiltiest 名词: guiltiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extract', '[\'ekstrækt]', 'vt.摘录；提取；拔出；榨出；选取 [计算机] 提取. n.摘录；精华；榨出物', '1. She extracted passages for the students to translate. 她选了些短文让学生翻译. 2. She extracted a small notebook from her handbag. 她从手提包里取出了一个小笔记本。 3. He tried to extract his pole from the mud. 他试图用力将杆子从泥中拔出来。 4. It takes a major operation to extract money from a minor poet. 要从小诗人那儿榨出钱来，得施行一次大手术。 5. I would like to quote two extracts from the book. 我很想引用这本书的两段文字。', '形容词: extractable 名词: extractor 过去式: extracted 过去分词: extracted 现在分词: extracting 第三人称单数: extracts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('render', '[\'rendər]', 'vt.提供；表现；使成为；宣布；翻译；回报；给予补偿；【计】渲染 n.粉刷；打底；交纳', '1. We are going to render them economic assistance. 我们打算向他们提供经济援助。 2. The power of the ocean was beautifully rendered in the poem. 这首诗将大海的力量表现得非常完美。 3. His back injury had rendered him unfit for work. 他的背伤使他无法胜任这份工作。 4. The jury has rendered its verdict. 陪审团已经作出了裁决', '形容词: renderable 名词: renderer 过去式: rendered 过去分词: rendered 现在分词: rendering 第三人称单数: renders');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('possess', '[pə\'zes]', 'vt.拥有；持有；支配', '1. Different workers possess different skills. 不同的工作者有不同的技能。 2. Rose is a woman who possesses a rare intelligence. 罗丝是一个拥有非凡智慧的女人。 3. The police asked me if I possessed a gun. 警察问我是否有枪。 4. She was possessed by the desire to be rich. 她被致富的欲望所支配。', '名词: possessor 过去式: possessed 过去分词: possessed 现在分词: possessing 第三人称单数: possesses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suburb', '[\'sʌbɜːrb]', 'n.郊区', '1. They proposed setting up a school in the suburb. 他们建议在这个郊区成立一所学校。 2. The factory is located in the suburb. 那家工厂坐落于郊区。 3. Ronaldo grew up in Bento Ribeiro, a suburb of Rio. 罗纳尔多在里约热内卢的一个叫本托. 4. Do not you think it would be nice to live in the suburb? 难道你不认为住在郊区是件好事吗？', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cipher', '[\'saɪfər]', 'n.密码；阿拉伯数字；零；暗号 v.计算；做算术；将 ... 写成密码', '1. The army uses a special cipher so that military messages are kept secret. 军队使用一种特殊密码,军事电讯因此得以保密。 2. The cipher took me three weeks before I hit it. 我费了3个多星期才把这密码解释出来。 3. Age is only a number, a cipher for the records. A man can\'t retire his experience. He must use it. Experience achieves more with less energy and time. 年龄只是个阿拉伯数字。一个人不能让他的经验退休。他必须用它。依靠经验，可以用较少的精力和时间获得更多。 4. I couldn\'t cipher out why she was there. 我搞不清她为什么会在那儿。', '过去式: ciphered 过去分词: ciphered 现在分词: ciphering 第三人称单数: ciphers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('newsletter', '[\'nuːzletər]', 'n.时事通讯；业务通讯，内部通讯；新闻信札', '1. She is reading an article in the club newsletter. 她正在读俱乐部时事通讯上的一篇文章。 2. The following appeared in a medical newsletter. 下述文字摘自一份医学时事通讯。 3. The Wild Animals Club is asking its members to write about this problem for the club newsletter. 野生动物俱乐部要其成员为俱乐部时事通讯写这些问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('ardor', '[\'ɑːdə]', 'n.热情；狂热；激情；灼热 =ardour(英).', '1. The difficulty and failure both didn\'t cool his ardor. 困难和失败都没有降低他的热情。 2. His political ardor led him into many arguments. 他的政治狂热使他多次卷入争论中。 3. She displayed great ardor for art. 她对艺术表现出极大的热心。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('resolved', '[rɪ\'zɑːlvd]', 'adj.下定决心的；断然的 动词resolve的过去式和过去分词形式.', '1. The union resolved to strike by 36 votes to 15. 工会以36票对15票通过决议举行罢工。 2. The discussion resolved itself into a pleasant chat. 讨论变成了愉快的闲聊。 3. She resolved that she would never see him again/never to see him again. 她决心不再见他。 4. If the dispute is to be resolved there must be some give and take. 若要争执获得解决，双方就要互相让步。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sodium', '[\'soʊdiəm]', 'n.钠', '1. Common salt is a compound of sodium and chlorine. 食盐是钠和氯的化合物。 2. Sodium and water react (together). 钠和水能起反应。', '简写符号: Na');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('autonomy', '[ɔː\'tɑːnəmi]', 'n.自治；自治权；自主', '1. The separatist is demanding full autonomy for their state. 分裂主义者在要求他们的州完全自治。 2. They are agitating to assert autonomy. 他们正在鼓吹实行自治。 3. The central government granted autonomy to a national minority. 中央政府对少数民族授予自治权。 4. County boroughs lose their autonomy. 自治郡失去了它们的自治权。', '名词: autonomist 名词复数: autonomies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inspect', '[ɪn\'spekt]', 'v.检查；视察', '1. Police were called out to keep at the airport, and inspect the arriving planes. 警察们被紧急召集起来去守卫机场，并对到达的飞机进行检查。 2. It was strange that nobody inspected my ticket before I got on the train. 很奇怪，我上火车前，竟然没有人查看我的车票。 3. Customs officers inspect our baggage. 海关人员检查我们的行李。 4. The government sent him to inspect our school. 政府派他来视察我们学校。', '形容词: inspective 过去式: inspected 过去分词: inspected 现在分词: inspecting 第三人称单数: inspects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shower', '[\'ʃaʊər]', 'n.淋浴；阵雨；送礼会；(大量)涌泻 v.冲(淋浴)；下(阵雨)；倾注', '1. She is taking a shower. 她正在洗淋浴。 2. Scattered showers are expected this afternoon. 预料今天下午有零星阵雨。 3. The weatherman predict shower this afternoon. 气象预告员说,今天下午有阵雨。 4. The neighbors held a bridal shower for the girl. 邻居为姑娘举行了一个准新娘送礼会。 5. I always shower after getting up. 起床后我总是洗个淋浴。', '形容词: showery 过去式: showered 过去分词: showered 现在分词: showering 第三人称单数: showers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('circumvent', '[ˌsɜːrkəm\'vent]', 'vt.绕行；设法避开；围住', '1. We went north in order to circumvent the mountains. 我们向北行驶为了从高山绕行。 2. She planned a way to circumvent all the bureaucratic red tape. 她计划避开官僚体制下的繁文缛礼。 3. The company has opened an office abroad in order to circumvent our tax laws. 公司在国外设立一个办事处，以躲避我国的税法。 4. There is a little island circumvented by a river. 这是河流环绕的小岛。', '形容词: circumventive 名词: circumventer 过去式: circumvented 过去分词: circumvented 现在分词: circumventing 第三人称单数: circumvents');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('theft', '[θeft]', 'n.偷窃', '1. Avarice drove him into theft. 贪婪驱使他偷窃。 2. The building has been insured against fire and theft. 这座大楼保了火险和失窃险。 3. The prosecutor brought an accusation of theft against him. 检察官指控他偷窃。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scornful', '[\'skɔːrnfl]', 'adj.轻蔑的；嘲笑的', '1. We are scornful of the forces of convention. 我们藐视习惯势力。 2. He gave a scornful laugh at my proposal. 他对我的建议轻蔑地一笑。 3. He felt humiliated by her scornful remarks. 他听到她那些嘲讽的话而感到屈辱。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('physician', '[fɪ\'zɪʃn]', 'n.内科医生', '1. He was attended by his personal physician. 他的私人医生护理他。 2. He prefers to be a surgeon rather than a physician. 他喜欢当外科医生而不愿作内科医生。 3. The physician put him on a special diet. 内科医生给他吃特定的食物。 4. He consulted his physician about his health. 他请医生诊断他的健康。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prolonged', '[prə\'lɔːŋd]', 'adj.持续很久的 prolong的过去式（分词）.', '1. The meeting may be prolonged into the evening because so many problems have to be solved tonight. 会议可能要延长到夜里，因为今晚有太多问题要解决。 2. After prolonged discussion, the representatives hammered out a form of words that was acceptable to everyone. 代表们经过长时间的讨论之后，终于想出一种大家都能接受的措辞方式。 3. The crowd burst into prolonged cheering. 人群中爆发出长时间的欢呼声。 4. After prolonged questioning, she finally confessed. 她受到长时间的盘问之后,终于承认了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('funding', '[\'fʌndɪŋ]', 'n.资金 动词fund的现在分词.', '1. This results in funding risk to the bank. 这会给银行带来资金筹措风险。 2. The project foundered after problems with funding. 这项计划因资金不足而失败。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dwindle', '[\'dwɪndl]', 'v.减少；缩小', '1. Those jobs will dwindle in years to come. 这些工作以后会逐年减少。 2. The number of Internet cafes is starting to dwindle. 网咖的数目正开始逐渐减少中。', '过去式: dwindled 过去分词: dwindled 现在分词: dwindling 第三人称单数: dwindles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('suitable', '[\'suːtəbl]', 'adj.适宜的；合适的', '1. These films are suitable for adults only. 这些电影只适宜成人观看。 2. All the students are assigned to suitable jobs. 所有的学生都分到了合适的工作。 3. The director is looking for a suitable locale for his new film. 导演在为新片物色合适的拍摄场地。', '副词: suitably 名词: suitability');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reflect', '[rɪ\'flekt]', 'v.反映；反射；反省；归咎；显示', '1. Her sad looks reflected the thought passing through her mind. 她忧戚的面容反映出她内心的思想。 2. The results reflect the greatest credit upon all concerned. 这些成绩带给所有有关人员最大的荣誉。 3. The sunlight was reflected in the water. 日光由水面反射出来。 4. I often reflect on the beauty and complexity of life. 我们经常思考人生的美丽与复杂。', '过去式: reflected 过去分词: reflected 现在分词: reflecting 第三人称单数: reflects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('luster', '[\'lʌstə]', 'n.光彩；荣誉；光泽 v.使 ... 发光辉；有光泽；发亮', '1. You ,like a nice girl, give off fascinating luster. 你像一位年轻的少女,放出迷人的光彩。 2. These pearls have a beautiful luster. 这些珍珠光泽很美。 3. The soft luster of the silk in the dim light was pleasing. 在暗淡的灯光下,那丝绸闪着柔和的光泽,十分悦目。', '过去式: lustered 过去分词: lustered 现在分词: lustering 第三人称单数: lusters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('miserable', '[\'mɪzrəbl]', 'adj.痛苦的；悲惨的；贫乏的；狼狈的', '1. Her wretchedness made him feel miserable. 她的不幸让他感到十分难受。 2. You made Grace Howland\'s life miserable. 你使格雷斯·豪兰的生活痛苦不堪。 3. The handmaid led a miserable life. 婢女过着悲惨的生活。 4. There are still many people whose living conditions are miserable. 仍有许多人的生活条件是很艰苦的。', '副词: miserably 名词: miserableness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('counselor', '[\'kaʊnsələ]', 'n.顾问；参事；法律顾问 =counsellor.', '1. The counselor gave us some disinterested advice. 顾问给了我们一些无私的忠告。 2. She is a marriage guidance counselor. 她是婚姻问题的顾问。 3. Counselor asked the witness question about his bank account. 法律顾问或律师问证人有关他银行账户的问题。', '名词: counselorship');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('oyster', '[\'ɔɪstər]', 'n.牡蛎', '1. That oyster closed up its valves. 那个牡蛎把壳合拢起来。 2. The man is as dumb as an oyster. 那人极少说话。 3. Oyster is the only seafood I like; I dislike the rest. 牡蛎是我唯一喜欢吃的海味; 其余的我都不喜欢。 4. After the damp weather all the drawers became as fast as a Kentish oyster. 湿季过后所有的抽屉都如肯特郡的牡蛎一般关得死死的。', '过去式: oystered 过去分词: oystered 现在分词: oystering 第三人称单数: oysters');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cosmos', '[\'kɑːzmoʊs]', 'n.宇宙 (复数）cosmos或cosmoses:大波斯菊.', '1. Our world is but a small part of the cosmos. 我们的世界仅仅是宇宙的一小部分而已。 2. Therefore, God projected the cosmos and souls. 因此，上帝投射了宇宙和灵魂。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stream', '[striːm]', 'n.(小)河；水流；(人；车；气)流；组 v.流动；流出；飘动；将(学生)按能力分组', '1. On either bank of the stream stand rows of willow trees. 小河两岸柳树成行。 2. Sand and leaves trapped the water in the stream. 沙子和树叶堵住了小河的水流。 3. Visitors to the exhibition came in an endless stream. 参观展览会的人络绎不绝。 4. Cars stream along the highway. 汽车在公路上流水般地行驶。', '形容词: streamy 过去式: streamed 过去分词: streamed 现在分词: streaming 第三人称单数: streams');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('homicide', '[\'hɑːmɪsaɪd]', 'n.杀人；杀人者', '1. He has been charged with homicide. 他被控告杀人。 2. Chicago set the homicide record. 芝加哥的杀人罪案创下了纪录。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('erode', '[ɪ\'roʊd]', 'vt.腐蚀；侵蚀；逐步毁坏，削弱，损害 vi.受到侵蚀', '1. Soft drinks erode your stomach lining. 软饮会腐蚀你的胃壁。 2. Memories are like stones, time and distance erode them like acid. 记忆犹如石头，时间和距离像酸一样腐蚀着它们。 3. Metals are eroded by acids. 金属易为酸所腐蚀。 4. The sea have erode the cliff face over the years. 海水经年累月冲刷著峭壁的表面。', '形容词: erodible 名词: erodibility 过去式: eroded 过去分词: eroded 现在分词: eroding 第三人称单数: erodes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('negotiate', '[nɪ\'ɡoʊʃieɪt]', 'vi.谈判；协商；交涉 vt.谈判达成；成功越过；议价出售', '1. We\'ve decided to negotiate with the employers about our wage claim. 我们决定就工资问题与雇主谈判。 2. We are happy to negotiate with you in that way. 我们很高兴用这种方式来和贵方协商交易。 3. Trade union leaders went back to negotiate with the government. 工会领导回去和政府进行交涉。 4. Since our contract is near its term we must negotiate a new one. 由于我们的合同快到期了，我们必须谈判新的合约。', '形容词: negotiatory 名词: negotiator 过去式: negotiated 过去分词: negotiated 现在分词: negotiating 第三人称单数: negotiates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proper', '[\'prɑːpər]', 'adj.合适的；正当的；真正的', '1. He could not come up with a proper answer. 他想不出一个合适的回答。 2. It\'s not proper for you to catch him up very short. 你突然打断他的话是不恰当的。 3. The company does not take proper fire precaution. 公司未采取正当的防火措施。 4. She hadn\'t had a proper holiday for years. 多年来她都没有过真正的假期。', '副词: properly 名词: properness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('choreographer', '[ˌkɒri\'ɒɡrəfə(r)]', 'n.舞蹈指导；编舞者', '1. She is a leading professional belly dance, choreographer, and teacher. 她既是杰出的专业肚皮舞演员，也是舞蹈指导和老师。 2. My choreographer keeps chiseling away at me, hoping to shape me into perfection. 我的舞蹈编导总是不断培养我,一心将我塑造成完美的舞蹈家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('affiliate', '[ə\'fɪlieɪt]', 'n.分公司；附属机构 vt.使隶属于；接纳；追溯 vi.发生联系', '1. It is an affiliate of the Red Cross. 它是红十字会的一个份子。 2. Do I get the product as part of the affiliate program? 我得到的附属产品作为节目? 3. I affiliate myself with their team to get more information on the share market. 我和他们组密切联系以获得更多股票市场的信息。 4. The Committee regrets that it cannot right now affiliate your group to their Society. 那个委员会很抱歉，不能马上将你们的团体并入他们的学会。 5. If we affiliate, we will have a better chance to win. 如果我们加入的话，赢的可能性更大。', '名词: affiliation 过去式: affiliated 过去分词: affiliated 现在分词: affiliating 第三人称单数: affiliates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inflation', '[ɪn\'fleɪʃn]', 'n.通货膨胀；膨胀', '1. The new government\'s prime task is to reduce the level of inflation. 新政府的主要任务是减低通货膨胀的水平。 2. The determinate factor of our economy is to control inflation. 我们经济的决定性因素是控制通货膨胀。 3. Farmers suffered from the price inflation. 价格膨胀让农民受害。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vice', '[vaɪs]', 'n.缺点；恶习；邪恶；罪行；生理缺陷 adj.副的；代理的 prep.代替 pref.代理的；副的 n.老虎钳', '1. He who thinks too much of his virtues reminds others of his vice. 念念不忘自己长处的人,会使别人想起他的缺点。 2. The vice of drinking is increasing. 酗酒之风正在增长。 3. Virtue and vice are two different things: the former leads to peace, the latter to misery. 美德与邪恶是不同的：前者带来和平,后者导致痛苦。 4. There is a lot of vices in big cities. 大城市存在许多道德败坏的行为。 5. He reported on the whole event to the vice premier. 他把整个事件向副总理作了汇报。 6. John was appointed postmaster vice Richard retired. 约翰被任命为邮政局长,取代退休的理查德。 7. She is vice-chair of the education committee. 她是教育委员会的代理主席。 8. The vice is bolted to the work-bench. 老虎钳是用螺栓拧在工作台上的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('astound', '[ə\'staʊnd]', 'v.使惊骇；使大吃一惊', '1. Her elopement astounded her parents. 她的私奔使她的父母大为震惊。 2. The figures revealed by the report are astounding. 这份报告透露的数字使人震惊。 3. The figures in that report astounded everyone. 那份报告中的数字让每个人大吃一惊。 4. We were astounded to read your letter. 我们看了你的信大吃一惊。', '副词: astoundingly 过去式: astounded 过去分词: astounded 现在分词: astounding 第三人称单数: astounds');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impose', '[ɪm\'poʊz]', 'v.强加；课征；强迫；征收(税款)', '1. I don\'t want to impose on you by staying too long. 我不想打扰你,不多耽搁了。 2. Do not try to impose your belief upon others. 别试图把你的信仰强加在别人头上。 3. We could not impose our own standards on others. 我们不能把我们的标准强加于他人。 4. He helped the Mongols impose taxes, interceding with the Khan to prevent reprisals when rebellions broke out. 因害怕在诺夫哥罗德人造反时遭到报复，他协助蒙古人征敛赋税。', '名词: imposer 过去式: imposed 过去分词: imposed 现在分词: imposing 第三人称单数: imposes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('orchid', '[\'ɔːrkɪd]', 'n.兰花；淡紫色', '1. The smell of the orchid is pleasant. 兰花的香味很宜人。 2. Many kinds of wild orchid are becoming rare. 很多种野生兰越来越罕见了。 3. She wore a single orchid on her evening dress. 她在晚礼服上缀着一朵兰花。 4. The wallpaper in our bedroom has a pattern of orchids. 我们卧室的壁纸是兰花图案的。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crust', '[krʌst]', 'n.外壳；坚硬的外壳；面包皮 vt.盖以硬皮 vi.结硬皮', '1. The earth\'s crust is layered.. 地球的外壳是分层的。 2. The crust on the snow was thick enough for us to walk on it. 外层的雪已经冻硬，可以在上面行走。 3. Please cut the bread into slices and remove the crust. 请将面包切片并去除外壳。 4. The crust of the bread is burnt. 这块面包的外皮烤焦了。 5. The snow crusted the lake last night. 昨夜的雪使湖面结了冰。 6. The snow may crust at night, due to outward radiation. 由于外部辐射，晚上雪可能结成雪壳。', '形容词: crustless 过去式: crusted 过去分词: crusted 现在分词: crusting 第三人称单数: crusts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nevertheless', '[ˌnevərðə\'les]', 'adv.尽管如此；不过；仍然 conj.然而；不过', '1. Our defeat was expected；nevertheless，it was disappointing. 我们的失败是意料中的事；尽管如此,还是令人失望。 2. We can\'t take your advice. Nevertheless, thank you for putting it. 我们不能接受您的建议。不过,谢谢您提出来。 3. Despite his injured ankle, he nevertheless succeeded in gaining the final against Germany. 尽管踝骨受伤,他仍然打入了与德国队的决赛。 4. Nevertheless as an exceptional measure, we have decided to overlook its late submission. 然而,作为一项特别措施,我们决定不计较逾期问题。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('reference', '[\'refrəns]', 'n.参考；参照；出处；推荐人；推荐函 v.注明出处；附参考资料', '1. This book is for reference only. 这本书仅供参考。 2. This frame of reference will be determined by the limitations on the rational man\'s knowledge. 这个参照系统决定于理性人知识的限制。 3. Full reference citations are available on the readings page. 全部参考资料的出处可以在阅读资料那页找到。 4. Can we contact your references? 我可以与你的推荐人联系吗? 5. Paraphrasing is not direct quotation, but you still need to reference it. 意译不是直接引用', '形容词: referential 副词: referentially 名词: referencer 过去式: referenced 过去分词: referenced 现在分词: referencing 第三人称单数: references');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spectrum', '[\'spektrəm]', 'n.系列；幅度；范围；光谱；[科]频谱', '1. There\'s a wide spectrum of opinions on this problem. 对这个问题的说法众说纷纭，莫衷一是。 2. There are tense competition in the whole spectrum of the industry. 整个工业领域竞争很激烈。 3. The press has published a wide spectrum of books. 这个出版社出版了一系列范围广泛的书籍。 4. In the spectrum, distinct colours shade into each other. 在光谱中，截然不同的颜色相互融合起来。', '名词复数: spectra');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fuzzy', '[\'fʌzi]', 'adj.毛茸茸的；模糊的；含糊不清的（感情）', '1. My hair is naturally wavy, so it gets fuzzy easily. 我的头发自然卷，所以容易毛茸茸的。 2. I tied it with fuzzy white yarn, and admired my work. 我用毛茸茸的白纱线把它系好，欣赏着我的杰作。 3. His thinking was superficial and fuzzy. 他的想法肤浅又模糊。 4. When we can see it, it appears as a fuzzy ball. 当我们能看到它时，似乎只看到一个模糊的球体。', '副词: fuzzily 比较级: fuzzier 最高级: fuzziest 名词: fuzziness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('methane', '[\'mɛθˌeɪn]', 'n.甲烷；沼气', '1. Cattle release methane when they digest their food. 牛在消化食物时,会释放出甲烷。 2. Natural bugs can turn out both hydrogen and methane. 天然的细菌可以生产氢气和甲烷。 3. Bacteria break down the animal waste to form methane gas. 细菌使动物粪便分解成沼气。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('slope', '[sloʊp]', 'n.倾斜；斜坡；斜面；斜率；斜线 vt.使倾斜 vi.倾斜；有坡度', '1. There is always a certain slope in a ship\'s deck. 船的甲板总有几分倾斜。 2. We slid down the grassy slope. 我们顺着草坡滑下去。 3. The hospital is on the eastward slope of the hill. 医院在小山的东坡。 4. There is no slope or angle to the croup. 在臀部没有斜面和角度。 5. They slope the grind so that the water can run away. 他们将地面铺得有坡度以便水能流泻。 6. The floor slopes badly here. 地板在这里倾斜得很厉害。', '副词: slopingly 名词: sloper 过去式: sloped 过去分词: sloped 现在分词: sloping 第三人称单数: slopes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inventory', '[\'ɪnvəntɔːri]', 'n.详细目录；存货(清单) vt.编制(详细目录)', '1. The job of compiling the inventory took several hours. 编辑详细目录的工作花了好几个小时。 2. The inventory showed that the store was overstocked. 清单显示商店存货过多。 3. All of the inventory has been tagged and referenced. 所有存货清单都被贴上了标签，以备参考。 4. Is the shop inventory verified before the commencement of a sales promotion? 有否在减价开始前按公司清单核实存货? 5. He inventories the minor losses and submitted it to the management. 他将那些较小的损失编进目录，上交给管理层。', '形容词: inventorial 副词: inventorially 名词复数: inventories 过去式: inventoried 过去分词: inventoried 现在分词: inventorying 第三人称单数: inventories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('symmetry', '[\'sɪmətri]', 'n.对称(性)；匀称；整齐', '1. These values constitute the symmetry waveform. 有这些数据来构成对称波形。 2. Many stems and roots show radial symmetry. 很多的茎和根都是辐射对称的。 3. His teeth spoiled the symmetry of his face. 他的牙齿破坏了他的面部匀称。 4. This addition may interfere with the symmetry of the layout. 这么一加，会破坏整个布局的匀称。', '名词复数: symmetries');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('wispy', '[\'wɪspi]', 'adj.小束的；细微的；模糊的', '1. A wisp of hair had escaped from under her hat. 一绺头发从她的帽下露出来。 2. A wisp of hair straggled across her ear. 一束头发散落在她耳朵上。 3. A small wisp or tuft,as of wool or cotton. 一束或一簇，如羊毛或棉花 4. A small wisp or tuft, as of wool or cotton. 一束或一簇，如羊毛或棉花', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('judgment', '[\'dʒʌdʒmənt]', 'n.裁判；判断；判断力；意见；判决书', '1. He passed judgment on the guilty man. 他对那个罪犯做出了裁决。 2. The soundness of his judgment has yet to be tested. 他的判断是否正确尚须验证。 3. Her decision seems to show a lack of political judgment. 她的决定似乎显示出缺乏政治判断力。 4. Sanity of judgment has never deserted him. 他从未失去明达的判断力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cohere', '[koʊ\'hɪr]', 'v.粘合；凝聚；前后一致；连贯', '1. When you squeeze a handful of snow,the flakes cohere to make a snowball. 你把一团雪捏紧，雪就黏合成雪球。 2. It can be difficult to get a group of people to cohere. 要使一群人凝聚在一起可能很困难。 3. This view does not cohere with their other beliefs. 这个观点与他们的其他看法不一致。 4. The adornments do not cohere with the basic design. 装饰物与设计的基调不协调。', '过去式: cohered 过去分词: cohered 现在分词: cohering 第三人称单数: coheres');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('latter', '[\'lætər]', 'adj.后者的；后面的', '1. I prefer the former design to the latter. 比起后者的设计方案,我更喜欢前者的。 2. One can travel there by ship or plane. Most people choose the latter. 乘船或乘飞机都可以到那,人们多选择后者。 3. The latter point is the most important. 后面提及的那一点是最重要的。 4. In the latter years of his life he lived alone and never welcomed visitors. 他晚年独居，从不欢迎来访者。', '副词: latterly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incoherent', '[ˌɪnkoʊ\'hɪrənt]', 'adj.不连贯的；语无伦次的', '1. This article is rather incoherent. 文章写得很不连贯。 2. I heard an incoherent mumble. 我听到了不连贯的低语声。 3. He was so drunk that he was quite incoherent. 他喝得这样醉，说起话来语无伦次。 4. The old man became incoherent as the disease got worse. 随着病情加重，老人变得语无伦次了。', '副词: incoherently 名词: incoherentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scratch', '[skrætʃ]', 'v.抓；搔（痒）；划破；划掉 n.抓痕；乱写；抓的声音；起跑线 adj.无让步的', '1. The dog is scratching at the door. 狗正在抓门。 2. He pretended to scratch his ear. 他假装搔耳朵。 3. I had to scratch my head to remember his name. 我只想苦苦地回忆他的名字。 4. Be careful not to scratch the furniture. 小心别刮坏家具。 5. There\'s a scratch on the side of my car. 我的汽车侧面有一道划痕。', '名词: scratcher 过去式: scratched 过去分词: scratched 现在分词: scratching 第三人称单数: scratches');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meteor', '[\'miːtiər]', 'n.流星；大气现象 abbr.气象学（=meteorology）', '1. A meteor suddenly shot across the sky. 一颗流星急速掠过天空。 2. It was made by a meteor that fell from space. 它是由流星从太空中坠落造成的。 3. Theoretically, their heir\'s theory of meteorology can explain the meteor. 从理论上讲，他们的继承人的气象理论能解释这种大气现象。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('application', '[ˌæplɪ\'keɪʃn]', 'n.应用；申请；专心；应用程序', '1. The application of new scientific discoveries to industrial production methods usually increases efficiency. 把新的科学发现运用到工业生产上,通常可以提高效率。 2. I didn\'t receive an acknowledgement of my application. 对我的申请,我还没有收到复信告知收悉。 3. The manager received twenty applications for the post. 经理收到了二十份求职申请书。 4. Patience and application will carry us through. 忍耐和专心会使我们度过难关。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('traitor', '[\'treɪtər]', 'n.叛徒；卖国贼；出卖朋友者', '1. The infamous traitor was sentenced to death. 那个罪大恶极的叛徒被判处死刑。 2. He struck a knife into the traitor\'s heart. 他将刀戳入卖国贼的心脏。 3. The traitor sold our important military secrets to the enemy. 这卖国贼把我方重要的军事秘密卖给敌人。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('intuition', '[ˌɪntu\'ɪʃn]', 'n.直觉；直觉的知识', '1. He takes his ground on intuition. 他的意见是凭直觉。 2. She sensed what was wrong by intuition. 她凭直觉意识到什么地方出毛病了。 3. It was said in a flash of intuition. 这话是凭一刹那的直觉说出的。 4. She had an intuition that her friend was ill. 她有一种直觉:她的朋友病了。', '形容词: intuitional 副词: intuitionally');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('altitude', '[\'æltɪtuːd]', 'n.高度；海拔；高地', '1. We are flying at an altitude of 20000 feet. 我们的飞行高度是20000英尺。 2. Air pressure decreases with altitude. 气压随海拔高度的增加而下降。 3. At this altitude there is no screening from the sun\'s rays. 在这种海拔高度，没有遮阳处。 4. At this altitude you often get strong winds. 在这一纬度地区，经常有大风。', '形容词: altitudinal');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('swan', '[swɑːn]', 'n.天鹅 vi.闲荡；游荡', '1. A black swan is rare. 黑天鹅很稀有。 2. The swan sings when death comes. 死期来到，天鹅歌声美妙。 3. The witch turned the princess into a swan. 巫婆把公主变成了一只天鹅。 4. Are you swanning off on holiday again? 你又是一走了之度假去了吗?', '过去式: swanned 过去分词: swanned 现在分词: swanning 第三人称单数: swans');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hatchet', '[\'hætʃɪt]', 'n.短柄小斧；战斧', '1. Hit and run raiders armed with a hatchet but wearing no armour for stealth. 萨卡特卡斯突袭者使用战斧轻装上阵，是游击战术的大师。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('successful', '[sək\'sesfl]', 'adj.成功的；圆满的', '1. She made a successful debut. 她初次登台获得成功。 2. He aims to be a successful writer. 他的目标是成为一个成功的作家。 3. They are highly successful in business. 他们经商非常成功。 4. We are confident of a successful outcome. 我们相信会有圆满的结果。', '副词: successfully 名词: successfulness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('foliage', '[\'foʊliɪdʒ]', 'n.叶子(总称)；簇叶', '1. Pollution has stripped the trees of their foliage. 污染剥光了这些树的叶子。 2. In summer the house next door is hidden luxuriant foliage. 夏天时，隔壁房子被繁茂的叶子所掩盖。', '形容词: foliaged');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lease', '[liːs]', 'n.租约；租契；租期 vt.出租；租得', '1. Our present lease on the flat expires next month. 我们这套公寓的租约下月到期。 2. An astute tenant always reads the small print in a lease. 精明的租户对租契上的每个细小之处都要讲究。 3. Does your current lease provide for showings prior to the tenant vacating the property? 您当前的租契是否规定了在房客搬出房间之前可以提前展售？ 4. The lease of my house has only a year to run . 我的房子的租约期限只有1年了。 5. This company leases out property. 这个公司出租房地产。', '形容词: leasable 名词: leaser 过去式: leased 过去分词: leased 现在分词: leasing 第三人称单数: leases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('analogy', '[ə\'nælədʒi]', 'n.类比；相似；类似', '1. It is not always reliable to argue by analogy. 用类推法论证并不总是可靠的。 2. He offers an analogy to explain how it works. 他用一个类比来解释这个过程。 3. He drew this conclusion on the analogy of yours. 他根据你的理论类推得出这个结论。 4. No analogy exists between you and me. 你和我之间没有相似之处。', '名词复数: analogies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('erase', '[ɪ\'reɪs]', 'v.抹去；擦掉；[计算机]擦除', '1. She couldn\'t erase the incident from her memory. 她难以忘记那次事件。 2. I did my best to erase the event from my memory. 我尽全力从记忆中抹去这件事。 3. There is no way to erase what I have done. I am sorry. 我所做的事已是无法抹去了。我很抱歉。 4. You can erase pencil marks with a rubber. 你可以用橡皮擦掉铅笔记号。', '形容词: erasable 名词: erasability 过去式: erased 过去分词: erased 现在分词: erasing 第三人称单数: erases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('incubate', '[\'ɪŋkjubeɪt]', 'v.孵；(细菌等)培养；逐渐发展；酝酿，深思；(传染病)潜伏', '1. The female bird incubates the eggs for about sixteen days while the male brings food. 雌鸟孵蛋差不多十六天，在这期间，雄鸟带回食物。 2. He incubated germs in a laboratory. 他在实验室中培养细菌。 3. The plans for revolution has long been incubating in their minds. 革命计划在他们心中酝酿已久。 4. The BSE bug incubates for three years. 疯牛病病毒的潜伏期为三年。', '形容词: incubative 过去式: incubated 过去分词: incubated 现在分词: incubating 第三人称单数: incubates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('relatively', '[\'relətɪvli]', 'adv.相对地；比较地', '1. Relatively speaking, it\'s a cold day today. 相对地说,今天是个寒冷的日子。 2. These industries are relatively new. 这些工业部门相对来说都是新型工业。 3. The exam was relatively easy. 这次考试比较容易。 4. The rabbit is a relatively recent introduction in Australia. 兔子在澳洲是较为近期引进的动物。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('constrict', '[kən\'strɪkt]', 'v.压缩；束紧；使收缩', '1. Doesn\'t that tight bracelet constrict your arm? 那个手镯那么紧不会压迫你的手臂吗? 2. Don\'t constrict your hair with tight hair bands and hats. 不要用紧绷绷的皮筋或帽子来固定头发。 3. Tight shoes constrict the feet. 鞋子太紧会挤脚。 4. Panic can constrict the blood vessels and impose an additional burden on the heart. 恐慌会使血管收缩，增加心脏负担。', '形容词: constrictive 副词: constrictively 过去式: constricted 过去分词: constricted 现在分词: constricting 第三人称单数: constricts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('decide', '[dɪ\'saɪd]', 'v.决定；判断；断定', '1. That decided me to leave my job. 那件事使我决定离职。 2. A chance meeting decided my career. 偶然的会面决定了我的事业。 3. He decided to get married. 他决定结婚。 4. Don\'t decide on important matters too quickly. 不要过于匆忙地对重要的事情作决定。', '形容词: decidable 名词: decidability 过去式: decided 过去分词: decided 现在分词: deciding 第三人称单数: decides');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prop', '[prɑːp]', 'n.支柱；支持者；倚靠人 n.道具 n.螺旋桨；推进器 v.支撑；维持', '1. The roof of the tunnel was supported by wooden props. 坑道顶用木柱支撑。 2. Mr. Helton was the hope and the prop of the family. 希尔顿先生成了一家的希望和支柱。 3. He was for several years the main prop and animator of Roosevelt himself. 他有几年是罗斯福本人的主要支持者和鼓舞者。 4. Her daughter was the only prop to the old lady during her illness. 她女儿是老太太病中唯一的依靠。 5. We will now add a prop model with physics properties. 我们现在添加有物理性的道具模型。 6. The wooden prop makes the machine look outdated. 木制螺旋桨的机器看起来过时了。 7. He propped his bicycle up against the fence. 他把脚踏车靠在篱笆上。', '过去式: propped 过去分词: propped 现在分词: propping 第三人称单数: props');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('announce', '[ə\'naʊns]', 'vt.宣布；宣告；预示；播报 vi.作播音员；宣布竞选', '1. I hope to announce the winner shortly. 我希望马上宣布胜利者的名字。 2. The president will announce a momentous decision. 主席将宣布重要决定。 3. We can go out to people and announce Good News. 我们能够走向人们，宣告天国的好消息。 4. I will always announce my goals to the world. 我要常常向世人宣告我的目标。 5. Cindy announces four programs a week. 辛迪一星期担任四个节目的播音员。', '过去式: announced 过去分词: announced 现在分词: announcing 第三人称单数: announces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('client', '[\'klaɪənt]', 'n.委托人；客户', '1. If a lawyer has plenty of clients, he grows rich. 律师如果有大量的诉讼委托人，就会财源不断。 2. The lawyer explained the legal technicalities to his client. 律师给委托人解释法律上的要点。 3. Counsel for the defence submitted that his client was clearly innocent. 被告的律师辩称其委托人显然是无辜的。 4. Now you can build the response to the client. 现在,您可以构建对客户端的响应。', '形容词: cliental 名词: clientage');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('adopt', '[ə\'dɑːpt]', 'v.采用；收养；接受', '1. They adopt new techniques in raising sheep. 他们采用新的养羊技术。 2. The schools must adopt new methods of teaching foreign languages. 学校应采用新的外语教学法。 3. She was left an orphan and a poor peasant woman adopted her. 她成了孤儿，一位贫农妇女收养了她。 4. To adopt the fruits of sin was to give countenance to it. 收养罪恶的果实就等于纵容罪恶。', '形容词: adoptable 名词: adopter 过去式: adopted 过去分词: adopted 现在分词: adopting 第三人称单数: adopts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('painstaking', '[\'peɪnzteɪkɪŋ]', 'adj.辛苦的；勤勉的；十分小心的 n.辛苦；苦心；工夫', '1. Planned or executed with painstaking attention to numerous parts or details. 精心制作的对众多部分或细节给予精心注意的计划或制作的', '副词: painstakingly');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('offensive', '[ə\'fensɪv]', 'adj.令人不快的；冒犯的；侮辱的；与进攻有关的 n.攻势；攻击', '1. His hasty temper made him offensive. 他急躁的脾气使他令人讨厌。 2. His remarks were rather offensive. 他的话非常无礼。 3. The boss kicked him out for an offensive remark. 老板因为他说了一句冒犯的话就把他开除了。 4. She has been greatly annoyed by his offensive remarks. 他出言不逊,这使她很反感。 5. In meetings she always takes the offensive before she can be criticized. 在会上，她不等别人批评她而总是先发制人。', '副词: offensively 名词: offensiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('static', '[\'stætɪk]', 'adj.静态的；静止的；稳定的；静力的；静电的 n.静电；静电干扰', '1. The winking eye is implemented as a series of static images. 眨动的眼睛是用一系列静态图像实现的。 2. Such principles as self-government, or freedom, or social welfare, are not static but dynamic. 自治,自由,或社会福利等原则并非静止,而是变动的。 3. House prices, which have been static for several months, are now rising again. 房价稳定了几个月，现在又上涨了。 4. Static friction is greater than sliding fricton. 静摩擦力大于滑动摩擦力。 5. Her hair was full of static. 她的头发上静电很强。', '形容词: statical 副词: statically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('electron', '[ɪ\'lektrɑːn]', 'n.电子', '1. Let us return to electron waves now. 现在我们再回到电子波上来。 2. An electron from one of the atom shells is ejected. 电子从原子的某一壳层中被弹射出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('deplete', '[dɪ\'pliːt]', 'vt.耗尽；使空竭', '1. Our stock of food is greatly depleted. 我们的食物储备已消耗殆尽。 2. Mankind must take care not to deplete the earth of its natural resources. 人类必须注意，切莫耗尽地球上的自然资源。 3. Wars in the region have depleted the country\'s food supplies. 这个地区的战争使国家的粮食供应空乏。 4. This expense has depleted our funds. 这笔花费已使我们的资金所剩无几。', '形容词: depletable 过去式: depleted 过去分词: depleted 现在分词: depleting 第三人称单数: depletes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('crumble', '[\'krʌmbl]', 'v.崩溃；弄碎；破灭', '1. The masonry of the old building began to crumble. 旧楼房的砖石结构开始崩落。 2. The earthquake made the wall sink and start to crumble. 这次地震把这堵墙震得下陷并开始崩塌。 3. He crumbled the bread in his fingers. 他用手指把面包捏碎了。 4. Even these hard parts may crumble to dust. 甚至这些坚硬的部分也会破碎成粉末。', '过去式: crumbled 过去分词: crumbled 现在分词: crumbling 第三人称单数: crumbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('range', '[reɪndʒ]', 'n.范围；射程；山脉；排；一系列；闲逛；炉灶；【数】值域，极差 v.排列；使…站在某一方；延伸；漫游；射程达到(某距离)', '1. The houses are sold out within this price range. 在这个价位范围之内的房子已售完。 2. It has come within the range of practical politics. 这就属于可实施性政治的范围了。 3. He used a whistle to decoy the birds within range. 他用口哨把鸟群诱至射程内。 4. She is still within range of my gun. 她仍在我枪炮的射程之内。 5. The shabby houses used to range along the road. 过去这路边破败的房子排成行。', '过去式: ranged 过去分词: ranged 现在分词: ranging 第三人称单数: ranges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enigmatic', '[ˌenɪɡ\'mætɪk]', 'adj.谜的；莫明其妙的；不可思议的', '1. She had an enigmatic smile on her face. 她脸上有谜般的微笑。 2. It\'s the most enigmatic pre-historic monument on earth . 它是地球上最神秘的史前遗迹。 3. Japan is thought to be an enigmatic country by foreigners. 日本被外国人认为是一个不可思议的国家。', '副词: enigmatically 异体字: enigmatical');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('inject', '[ɪn\'dʒekt]', 'v.注射；注入；引入；插入', '1. The nurse injected penicillin into her arm. 护士给她的胳膊注射了青霉素。 2. His medicine is a drug that can be injected or taken by mouth. 他的药可以注射或口服。 3. His appointment may inject some new life into the committee. 他的任命可能给这委员会注入新生命。 4. He injected new ideas into the discussion. 他把新的概念引入讨论中。', '名词: injector 过去式: injected 过去分词: injected 现在分词: injecting 第三人称单数: injects');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hieroglyph', '[\'haɪərəɡlɪf]', 'n.象形文字；图画文字；秘密文字', '1. As a hieroglyph this symbol represents the unification of Upper and Lower Egypt. 如一个象形文字那样，这个符号表现了上埃及和下埃及的统一。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('grain', '[ɡreɪn]', 'n.谷物；谷类；微量；颗粒；纹理；格令 v.形成(颗粒)；(用谷物)喂养', '1. We ship grain to Africa. 我们把谷物运往非洲。 2. There are a few grains of rice in a bowl. 碗中有几颗米粒。 3. There isn\'t a grain of truth in it. 那事无丝毫真实性。 4. The coffee was good, but thick with grains. 咖啡很好, 但满是粒子。 5. Physical isolation goes against the corporate grain, the hierarchy being organized around the office. 身体上的隔绝违反合作意愿，使办公室周围形成特定阶层。', '名词: grainer 过去式: grained 过去分词: grained 现在分词: graining 第三人称单数: grains');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('unfortunately', '[ʌn\'fɔːrtʃənətli]', 'adv.不幸地；遗憾地', '1. Unfortunately, I missed the last train. 我不幸错过了末班火车。 2. Unfortunately, I hurt my knee when I fell down on the ice. 真不幸，我在冰上摔倒时摔伤了膝盖。 3. Unfortunately I am not aware of that. 遗憾的是，我不知道此事。 4. Unfortunately, the restaurant he recommended fell far short of our expectations. 遗憾的是,他推荐的餐厅与我们心目中的相去甚远。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('boon', '[buːn]', 'n.恩惠；所感激的事 adj.合得来的', '1. This baby is a great boon to the Smith family. 这个宝宝是老天赐给史密斯家的宝贝。 2. Remember the hurt that we give to others, forget the boon. 记住自己对别人的伤害，忘掉自己对别人的恩惠。 3. A priest accompanying your regiment into the fray is indeed a boon. 对于你的师团来说，有一名牧师与你的部队一同冲杀敌阵，着实是一种恩惠。 4. Park is a great boon to people in big city. 在大城市里，公园是人们的好去处。 5. He has a couple of boon companions. 他有几个爱吃喝交际的朋友。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('marsh', '[mɑːrʃ]', 'n.沼泽；湿地 Marsh：马什（人名）.', '1. There are a lot of frogs in the marsh. 沼泽里有许多青蛙。 2. Be careful not to get stuck in the marsh. 小心别陷进沼泽里。 3. No retrieval romps in the marsh. 在湿地不好游戏。 4. At the mouth of the river, there is a large area of marsh. 这条河流的入口有一大片湿地。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cassette', '[kə\'set]', 'n.盒式磁带；暗盒', '1. Cassette tape recorders are gradually out of date now. 现在,盒式磁带录音机渐渐过时了。 2. He bought a new cassette recorder. 他买了一台新的盒式录音机。 3. There is a little window in the cassette case so that you can see the tape. 盒式音像带上有个小窗，能看见里面的磁带。 4. I rewound the cassette and played her voice back to her. 我把录音带转回去，把她的声音放给她听。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('beak', '[biːk]', 'n.鸟嘴；鸟嘴状物体；<非>鹰钩鼻 n.<英俚>地方治安官；校长', '1. This parrot has a red beak. 这只鹦鹉的嘴是红色的。 2. The male\'s orange beak differentiates it from the female. 那种鸟雄鸟的喙呈橙色，与雌鸟不同。 3. The bird picked a hole in the ice with its beak. 那鸟在冰上啄出了一个洞。', '形容词: beaked');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bare', '[ber]', 'adj.赤裸的；空的；仅有的；贫瘠的，荒芜的 vt.使裸露；暴露', '1. The fierce sun parched the bare earth. 灼热的阳光炙烤着光秃秃的大地。 2. The boy likes to walk on the sand with bare feet. 这男孩喜欢赤脚在沙滩上走。 3. The little room was almost bare of furniture. 这个小房间几乎没有什么家俱。 4. A bare word would be enough for me. 对我来说一句话就够了。 5. He bared the tree of its bark. 他剥光树皮。', '比较级: barer 最高级: barest 名词: bareness 过去式: bared 过去分词: bared 现在分词: baring 第三人称单数: bares');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('surpass', '[sər\'pæs]', 'vt.超越；胜过', '1. To be in love is to surpass oneself. 人在爱中超越自我。 2. You seem to surpass yourself in this painting. 你在这幅画的创作上似乎超越了你自己。 3. Her sweetness nothing can surpass. 温柔甜蜜世无双。 4. It is hard to surpass Evans in speed. 要在速度上胜过艾文斯很难。', '过去式: surpassed 过去分词: surpassed 现在分词: surpassing 第三人称单数: surpasses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('temperance', '[\'tempərəns]', 'n.节欲；禁酒；节制', '1. Temperance is the best physic. 节欲是灵丹妙药。 2. The temperance league wanted to close all the saloons in town. 禁酒联合会要关闭镇上所有的酒吧。 3. In the temperance question, Mr White takes his stand on total abstinence. 在戒酒问题上，怀特先生是主张完全戒掉。 4. Temperance is the greatest of virtues. 自我节制是最大的美德。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('phase', '[feɪz]', 'n.相位；方面；局面；阶段；时期 vt.逐步执行', '1. No phase transition evidence is found. 没有发现任何相位跃迁的证据。 2. Distortion can result from phase shifts. 相位变化将造成失真。 3. This is but one phase of the subject. 这仅是问题的一个方面。 4. They are talking about the changing phases of society. 他们谈论着不断变化的社会状况。 5. The use of lead-free petrol is now being phased in. 无铅汽油的应用现正逐步推广。', '形容词: phasic 过去式: phased 过去分词: phased 现在分词: phasing 第三人称单数: phases');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embalm', '[ɪm\'bɑːm]', 'v.铭记；防腐；使弥香气；使不朽', '1. We will embalm him forever. 我们永远怀念他。 2. We must embalm the master\'s wise opinions. 这位大师的崇论闳议，我们一定要铭记于心。 3. Thousands of years ago in Egypt, salt was used to embalm the dead. 千万年前埃及人曾利用盐涂尸防腐。', '名词: embalmer 过去式: embalmed 过去分词: embalmed 现在分词: embalming 第三人称单数: embalms');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stadium', '[\'steɪdiəm]', 'n.体育场；运动场；[生]期', '1. The crowds drifted away from the stadium. 人群慢慢从体育场散去。 2. Keep on past the church; the stadium is about half a mile further on. 一直向前走过了教堂，约莫半英里就是体育场。 3. We will go to the stadium to watch a football match. 我们将去体育场观看足球比赛。 4. The takings at the football stadium has fallen off. 足球运动场的收入减少了。', '名词复数: stadiums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('permanent', '[\'pɜːrmənənt]', 'adj.永久的；持久的 n.<口> 烫发', '1. The incident left permanent traces on his mind. 那件事在他头脑里留下了永久的印象。 2. I am looking for a permanent position. 我在找一个永久性的职业。 3. These factors usually have a longer and more permanent impact on share prices. 这项因素通常会对股价产生更加长远和持久的影响。', '副词: permanently 名词: permanentness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('invade', '[ɪn\'veɪd]', 'v.侵略；拥入；侵害；侵扰', '1. When did the Romans invade Britain? 古罗马人是何时侵略英国的? 2. The town was invaded by reporters. 这个城市涌进了大批记者。 3. In the summer tourists invade the mountain village. 夏天游客成群结队地到这个山村来。 4. Germs may invade the organism. 细菌会侵入有机体。', '名词: invader 过去式: invaded 过去分词: invaded 现在分词: invading 第三人称单数: invades');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('vestige', '[\'vestɪdʒ]', 'n.丝毫；遗迹；痕迹；退化的器官', '1. There is not a vestige of truth in the report. 该报告毫无真实性。 2. There had not a vestige of the abbey remains. 修道院的遗迹已荡然无存。 3. Some upright stones in wild place are the vestige of ancient religion. 荒原上一些直立的石块是古老宗教的遗迹。 4. Every vestige has been swept away. 一切痕迹都被一扫而光。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advertise', '[\'ædvərtaɪz]', 'v.登广告；宣传；告知', '1. We decided to advertise our new product. 我们决定为我们的新产品做广告。 2. We can advertise on the Internet. 我们可以在网上登广告。 3. I must advertise for a new secretary. 我得刊登广告聘请一位新秘书。 4. It was time to advertise our cause instead of our cars. 当时的当务之急是我们的事业可不是为我们的汽车进行广告宣传。', '名词: advertiser 过去式: advertised 过去分词: advertised 现在分词: advertising 第三人称单数: advertises');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fickle', '[\'fɪkl]', 'adj.变幻无常的；易变的', '1. The weather\'s so fickle in summer. 夏日的天气如此多变。 2. It\'s the third time that he changed his mind; he\'s so fickle! 他改变主意已经是第三回了,他这人太反复无常了！ 3. The television world was a notoriously fickle one. 电视圈是出了名的变化无常。 4. He turned out to be fickle - he has left me. 他原来是个善变的人 - 他离开我了。', '副词: fickly 名词: fickleness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spur', '[spɜːr]', 'n.支脉；刺激；马刺；鞭策 vt.刺激；鞭策；促进', '1. She went to London on the spur of the moment. 她一时兴起就到伦敦去了。 2. International competition was a spur to modernization. 国际竞争是实现现代化的动力。 3. A good heart horse often needs a good spur. 好马常需好靴刺。 4. The thought of the prize was the spur for the team. 夺取锦标的想法是该队的动力。 5. What spurred her to do that? 是什么促使她那么干的？', '过去式: spurred 过去分词: spurred 现在分词: spurring 第三人称单数: spurs');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pervasive', '[pər\'veɪsɪv]', 'adj.普遍的；渗透的；遍布的', '1. Involuntary unemployment is pervasive. 非自愿性失业普遍出现。 2. It is the most pervasive compound on earth. 它是地球上最普遍的化合物。 3. TV is the most powerfull and pervasive of the media. 电视是传播媒介中最强大和最有渗透力的。 4. A sense of social change is pervasive in her novels. 她的小说里充斥着社会变化的意识。', '副词: pervasively 名词: pervasiveness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sprout', '[spraʊt]', 'v.长芽；萌芽；迅速成长 n.芽；年幼者', '1. The seeds will sprout in a few days. 这些种子几天后就会发芽。 2. These potatoes have begun to sprout. 这些马铃薯开始发芽了。 3. The seeds sprout into small, hairlike seedings. 种子发育成小小的、毛茸茸的幼苗。 4. He sprouted up six inches a year. 他一年长高了六英寸。 5. In spring, here, drizzle moistens land , also feed rice sprout. 春天，这里细雨蒙蒙，滋润着土地，也哺育着稻苗。', '过去式: sprouted 过去分词: sprouted 现在分词: sprouting 第三人称单数: sprouts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('salvage', '[\'sælvɪdʒ]', 'vt.救助；打捞；抢救 n.海上救助；打捞；抢救', '1. The government tried to salvage several business companies from bankruptcy. 政府设法把这几个商业公司从破产境地中拯救出来。 2. They are trying to salvage the wrecked ship. 他们努力抢救遇难的船只。 3. All attempts to salvage the wrecked ship failed. 抢救失事船只的一切努力都失败了。 4. It is time for Morrison to salvage his career. 这是莫里森拯救他职业生涯的时代。 5. Salvage of the wreck is made difficult by bad weather. 船遇难後因天气恶劣救援工作十分困难。', '形容词: salvageable 名词: salvageability 过去式: salvaged 过去分词: salvaged 现在分词: salvaging 第三人称单数: salvages');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fulfill', '[fʊl\'fɪl]', 'vt.完成；履行；执行；满足', '1. Whatever happens I\'m determined to fulfill it. 不管发生什么,我都决心完成它。 2. How they laid about them to fulfill the task! 他们是何等竭尽全力来完成这一任务啊！ 3. You must fulfill your promise. 你必须履行诺言。 4. The doctor\'s instructions must be fulfilled exactly. 必须一丝不苟地遵照医嘱去办。', '名词: fulfiller');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sturdy', '[\'stɜːrdi]', 'adj.强健的；坚固的；坚决的', '1. The sturdy young man removed the rock without effort. 那个壮实的小伙子没费多大劲便把石块搬开了。 2. His son has grown up into a sturdy hardworking young man. 他的儿子已成长为一个健壮勤劳的小伙子。 3. That chair doesn\'t look very sturdy. 椅子看上其不坚固。 4. Have you any sturdy hiking boots? 有没有耐用的健行靴？', '副词: sturdily 比较级: sturdier 最高级: sturdiest 名词: sturdiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('snobbish', '[\'snɑːbɪʃ]', 'adj.势利的；自命不凡的', '1. Everyone was annoyed by his snobbish attitude. 所有的每个人都对他势利的态度反感。 2. Jane feels she can never compete with these snobbish, elegant people. 简·爱感到她永远无法同这些高雅却势利的人们竞争。 3. It is strange that he should fall in love with such a snobbish girl. 说来真怪，他居然与那位高傲的女孩子坠入情网。', '副词: snobbishly 名词: snobbishness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('sharpen', '[\'ʃɑːrpən]', 'vt.使尖锐；磨快；加剧 vi.变尖锐', '1. My pencil is blunt, could you lend me a knife to sharpen it? 我的铅笔钝了，你能借我把刀子削一削吗？ 2. Generations of urban living sharpened their wits. 世代居住在城市里使他们磨练了才智。 3. Strikes will sharpen the country\'s dilemma. 罢工将加剧这个国家的困境。 4. The soldiers sharpened up their knives. 战士们把刀磨得锋利。', '名词: sharpener 过去式: sharpened 过去分词: sharpened 现在分词: sharpening 第三人称单数: sharpens');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hum', '[hʌm]', 'n.嗡嗡声；哼声；杂声 v.发低哼声；哼(曲子)；活跃 int.哼；嗯（用以表示犹豫）', '1. He could hear the hum of the bees in the garden. 他听得见花园里蜜蜂的嗡嗡声。 2. His strong voice cut through the hum of conversation like a knife through butter. 他那宏亮有力的声音一下子压倒了嗡嗡的谈话声。 3. The background with all of my phones is totally silent, no hiss, hum at all, just total blackness. 背景与我的所有电话，是完全沉默，没有噪音，哼声一切，在刚刚共有黑。 4. She heard the hum of voices in the house. 她听见了屋子里的嘈杂声。 5. You don\'t need to sing loud, you just hum softly. 你不必大声唱,只要轻轻哼就好了。 6. Hum, you\'re joking! 哼，你在开玩笑吧！', '形容词: hummable 名词: hummer 过去式: hummed 过去分词: hummed 现在分词: humming 第三人称单数: hums');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gourd', '[ɡʊrd]', 'n. 葫芦； <俚> 脑瓜', '1. The gourd is the key which opens a rich door. 葫芦是打开富贵门的钥匙。 2. With a shaldng hand he reached inside his quilt and brought out his pottery gourd. 他的手哆嗦着，把闷葫芦罐儿从被子里掏了出来。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('purge', '[pɜːrdʒ]', 'n.整肃；清除；泻药；净化 v.净化；清除；清洗', '1. The new president carried out a purge of disloyal army officers. 新总统对不忠诚的陆军军官进行了一次整肃。 2. The Red Guards carried out the purge too enthusiastically, often acting without close direction from Peking. 红卫兵非常狂热地贯彻执行了清除，横扫了北京的各个方面。 3. The medicine was an effective purge. 这是疗效很好的泻药。 4. We may purge water by distillation. 我们可以用蒸馏法使水净化。 5. We may purge water by distillation. 我们可以用蒸馏法使水净化。', '名词: purger 过去式: purged 过去分词: purged 现在分词: purging 第三人称单数: purges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('complementary', '[ˌkɑːmplɪ\'mentri]', 'adj.补充的；互补的', '1. His personality is complementary to hers. 他的个性与她的相反相成。 2. The two viewpoints are complementary and both approaches are of interest. 这两种方法是互为补充的而且都是有价值的。 3. Red and green are complementary colors. 红色和绿色是互补色。 4. Our two countries are mutually complementary in economy. 我们两国的经济是互补的。', '副词: complementarily 名词: complementariness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('caliber', '[\'kæləbə]', 'n.才干；口径', '1. There is no other player even remotely approaching her caliber. 就才干而言，其他选手远远赶不上她。 2. I consider him a genius of the same caliber as Kurosawa or Fellini. 我认为他的才干是等同于黑泽明和费里尼的天才之流。 3. The caliber of the vein and the artery to which it was anastomosed was similar. 用同等口径的动静脉吻合。 4. The moderate caliber enables the blood fluidity change to express precisely. 适中的口径又使血液流动性变化得以精确表达。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gossip', '[\'ɡɑːsɪp]', 'n.流言蜚语；爱说长道短的人；闲话 vi.散播(流言蜚语)', '1. There has been much gossip in political circles. 政界里有许多流言蜚语。 2. I loathe people who spread malicious gossip. 我讨厌那些散布充满恶意的流言蜚语的人。 3. He\'s a terrible gossip. 他专爱说人闲话。 4. I have no time to engage in gossip. 我无暇闲聊。 5. She loves to gossip to her neighbors. 她喜欢议论邻居们的是非长短。', '形容词: gossipy 名词: gossiper 过去式: gossiped 过去分词: gossiped 现在分词: gossiping 第三人称单数: gossips');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('magnet', '[\'mæɡnət]', 'n.磁铁；有吸引力的人（物）', '1. He picked all the pins up with a magnet. 他用磁铁捡起了所有的大头针。 2. He was deeply attracted by the delicate cast of her features. 他的前途取决于这一机会。 3. Forbidden City is a great magnet for foreign tourists. 紫禁城对外国旅游者来说是个有巨大吸引力的地方。 4. The beautiful actress was the magnet that drew great audiences. 那个漂亮的女演员对很多观众都很有吸引力。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hinge', '[hɪndʒ]', 'n.铰链；关键 vt.用铰链装 vi.依情况而定', '1. The two bones are articulated like a hinge. 这两块骨头由关节铰链般连接起来。 2. Rust is eating away the iron hinge. 铁锈正腐蚀着铁铰链。 3. This was the hinge of fate of the whole campaign. 这是决定整场战役命运的关键点。 4. Your arm should hinge from the shoulder. 你的手臂应该像从肩膀铰链住一般。 5. His acceptance will hinge upon the term. 他接受与否将依条件而定。', '过去式: hinged 过去分词: hinged 现在分词: hinging 第三人称单数: hinges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('directory', '[də\'rektəri]', 'n.目录；工商名录；指南 adj.给予指导的', '1. He thumbed through the directory to look for her number. 他翻阅电话号码簿找寻她的号码。 2. He found their address in the telephone directory. 他在电话薄里找到了他们的住址。 3. And here is our service directory. 这是服务指南。', '名词复数: directories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pattern', '[\'pætərn]', 'n.模式；图案；典范；式样 v.以图案装饰；仿造；模仿', '1. The two buildings are modeled after the same pattern. 这两座建筑是按照同一模式建造的。 2. Training and education follow different patterns in different regions. 培训和教育在不同的地区遵循不同的模式。 3. This cloth has a pattern of blue and white squares. 这种布有蓝白格子的图案。 4. Threads of different colors and textures were woven into an intricate pattern. 各种花色和质地的线织成了一幅复杂的图案。 5. I like the carpets patterned with peonies. 我喜欢印有牡丹花图案的地毯。', '过去式: patterned 过去分词: patterned 现在分词: patterning 第三人称单数: patterns');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('closet', '[\'klɑːzət]', 'n.壁橱；衣帽间；密室；厕所 adj.隐藏的；不公开的；空谈的 vt.把 ... 关在房间里', '1. Put the coats back into the closet. 请把大衣放回到壁橱里。 2. You may put these books in the closet. 你可以把这些书放在壁橱里。 3. The Prince\'s bedroom is large, but his closet is larger. 王子的卧室也很大,不过他的衣帽间则更大。 4. The loser closely enclosed himself in the closet. 那个失败者把自己严密地封闭在小室内。 5. We must guard against closet racists. 我们必须警惕隐蔽的种族主义者。 6. He used to closet himself with a book. 过去他常把自己关在小房间里读书。', '名词: closetful 过去式: closeted 过去分词: closeted 现在分词: closeting 第三人称单数: closets');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('enigma', '[ɪ\'nɪɡmə]', 'n.难以理解的事物；谜；谜一般的人', '1. I\'ve known him for many years, but he remains something of an enigma to me. 我与他相识多年，他仍然难以捉摸。 2. It is an enigma to me. 它对我来说是个迷。 3. It is the enigma of life itself that you desire me to solve. 你要我解决的是人生之谜。 4. Faraway space is an enigma to people. 遥远的太空对人类来说是一个谜。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('dogmatic', '[dɔːɡ\'mætɪk]', 'adj.教条的；武断的', '1. Dogmatic criticism settles nothing. 教条主义的批评不能解决问题。 2. It rejects all dogmatic and speculative assertions in philosophy. 它摈弃哲学中一切教条的和思辨的主张。 3. You can\' t be dogmatic in matters of taste. 对于个人爱好的事,你不能这样自以为是。 4. Leaders are flexible rather than dogmatic. 领导者处事灵活而不武断。', '副词: dogmatically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('spectacle', '[\'spektəkl]', 'n.景象；场面；奇观；壮观；公开展示；表相，假相 n.（复）眼镜', '1. The sunrise was a splendid spectacle. 日出是个壮观的景象。 2. The celebrations provided a magnificent spectacle. 庆祝活动呈现一派宏伟的景象。 3. The carnival parade was a magnificent spectacle. 狂欢节游行场面热烈，蔚为大观。 4. The children took in the spectacle open-mouthed. 孩子们张着嘴注视精彩表演。 5. I can\'t see things through your spectacles. 我和你的看法不同。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hunger', '[\'hʌŋɡər]', 'n. 饥饿； 渴望 v. 饿； 渴望； 使 ... 饥饿', '1. He was goaded by hunger into stealing. 他为饥饿所迫而行窃。 2. I had experienced the pangs of hunger. 我曾经历过饥饿的折磨。 3. His hunger for knowledge drove him to the library. 他对求知的强烈渴望驱使他上图书馆。 4. My hunger for magic is clouding my judgement! 我对魔法的渴望已经淡化了我的判断力。 5. Hunger gives relish to simple food. 肚子饿时吃什么都香。', '过去式: hungered 过去分词: hungered 现在分词: hungering 第三人称单数: hungers');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('congestion', '[kən\'dʒestʃən]', 'n.阻塞；拥挤；充血', '1. Congestion frequently reduces traffic to walking pace. 交通阻塞经常把车流的速度降低得如步行一般缓慢。 2. Congestion really is a long-standing problem in Beijing. 交通阻塞的确是北京的老大难。 3. The route was designed to relieve traffic congestion. 这条路是为缓解交通拥挤而开辟的。 4. Nose drops often relieve nasal congestion. 滴鼻剂常可缓解鼻腔充血。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lace', '[leɪs]', 'n.鞋带；饰带；花边；缎带 v.系带子；饰以花边；把酒搀入；<口>抨击', '1. He stopped to do up his shoe lace. 他停下来把鞋带系上。 2. My shoe lace keeps coming undone. 我的鞋带老是松开。 3. My daughter wears a dress embellished with lace and ribbons today. 今天我女儿穿了一件有花边和饰带的连衣裙。 4. She wears a dress with delicate lace. 她穿了一件带有精致花边的裙子。 5. If you don\'t lace up your shoes, you\'ll trip over. 如果你不系好鞋带，你会被绊倒的。', '形容词: laceless 名词: lacer 过去式: laced 过去分词: laced 现在分词: lacing 第三人称单数: laces');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('repulse', '[rɪ\'pʌls]', 'n.击退；拒绝 v.击退；拒绝', '1. After the second repulse, the enemy surrendered. 在第二次击退之后，敌人投降了。 2. Her repulse was quite unexpected. 她的拒绝是完全出人意料的。 3. Her request for a donation met with a rude repulse. 她要求赞助却遭到粗暴拒绝。 4. Do I repulse you with my queasy smile? 我诡异的笑脸让你知难而退了吗？', '名词: repulser 过去式: repulsed 过去分词: repulsed 现在分词: repulsing 第三人称单数: repulses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('cleanse', '[klenz]', 'v.使 ... 清洁；净化；使 ... 纯洁', '1. The nurse cleansed the wound before stitching it. 护士在缝合伤口前先清洁一下伤口。 2. Health experts are trying to cleanse the air in cities. 卫生专家们正设法净化城市里的空气。 3. May God cleanse my wickedness. 愿上帝洗净我的邪恶。', '过去式: cleansed 过去分词: cleansed 现在分词: cleansing 第三人称单数: cleanses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lyric', '[\'lɪrɪk]', 'adj.抒情的 n.抒情诗；歌词', '1. The anthology reveals a prejudice in favour of lyric poets. 这部选集显示出对抒情诗人有所偏爱。 2. His earlier work announced a lyric talent of the first order. 他的早期作品显露了一流的抒情才华。 3. He is a fine writer of lyrics. 他是个优秀的抒情诗作家。 4. I\'m deeply moved by this lyric of Shelley\'s. 我被雪莱的这首抒情诗深深打动了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('shield', '[ʃiːld]', 'n.盾；盾状物；防卫物 vt.保护；庇护', '1. The shield protected him from the blows of his enemy. 这盾牌保护他免受敌人的打击。 2. There is a shield in the badge of PLA men. 解放军的徽章上有着盾状物。 3. He must pile more sand on top as a shield. 他必须在顶上多加些沙土作为防御物。 4. Motorcyclists must wear helmets to shield them from injury. 摩托车手必须戴头盔保护自己免受伤害。', '名词: shielder 过去式: shielded 过去分词: shielded 现在分词: shielding 第三人称单数: shields');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('appoint', '[ə\'pɔɪnt]', 'v.任命；委派；指定；约定', '1. The company decided to appoint a new treasurer. 公司决定任命一位新司库。 2. They appointed him chairman. 他们任命他为主席。 3. As a top manager, he should appoint none but people on their merit. 作为一位总经理，他应该任人为贤。 4. We must appoint a new teacher soon. 我们必须尽快委派一个新教师。', '过去式: appointed 过去分词: appointed 现在分词: appointing 第三人称单数: appoints');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('alchemist', '[\'ælkəmɪst]', 'n.炼丹术士；炼金术士', '1. The alchemist should have come by now. 炼金术士该来了。 2. The alchemist was standing over him. 炼金术士正在他面前站立着。 3. At first glance, it all seems an alchemist\'s illusion. 乍看上去，它完全象是一位炼金术士的幻术。', '形容词: alchemistic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('liquid', '[\'lɪkwɪd]', 'adj.液体的；液态的；清澈的；清脆的；已转化成现款的（财） n.液体', '1. The doctor recommended that the patient be fed liquid food. 医生建议病人应吃流质食物。 2. Air whether in the gaseous or liquid state is a fluid. 空气，无论是气态的还是液态的，都是一种流体。 3. The earth is believed to have a liquid core. 人们相信地球有一个液态核。 4. Kate is a pretty girl with large liquid eyes. 凯特是一个有一双水汪汪大眼睛的漂亮姑娘。 5. Plasma is clear yellow liquid. 血浆是种透明淡黄的液体。', '副词: liquidly 名词: liquidness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('display', '[dɪ\'spleɪ]', 'n.显示；陈列；炫耀 vt.显示；表现；夸示', '1. Let\'s display the figures and see what we have. 通过显示一下数字看看我们能看到什么。 2. The bottles of whisky on display are all dummies. 所陈列的威士忌酒都是假的。 3. There will be a display of bronze statuary in this museum next week. 下星期这个博物馆将举办一个青铜雕塑作品展览。 4. He made a display of his learning. 他夸耀自己有学问。 5. I have rarely seen her display any sign of emotion. 我难得见到她将喜怒形于色。', '过去式: displayed 过去分词: displayed 现在分词: displaying 第三人称单数: displays');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('husbandry', '[\'hʌzbəndri]', 'n.农事；耕作；农牧业；节约（资源）', '1. The development of agriculture and animal husbandry has been given top priority in the Tibetan economy. 发展农牧业在西藏的经济生活中处于最重要的地位。 2. Over years, Jieqi has played an important role in China\'s agricultural and animal husbandry production. 长期以来，二十四节气在中国的农牧业生产中一直起着重要的作用。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('multitude', '[\'mʌltɪtuːd]', 'n.大量；多数；群众', '1. A multitude of heroic figures emerge. 大量英雄人物出现了。 2. An angry multitude collected in the street. 街道上聚集了一大群愤怒的人。 3. There are a multitude of reasons against it. 有许多反对理由。 4. The multitude may laugh at his music, but we know better. 一般人也许会嘲笑他的音乐，但我们更了解它。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('elapse', '[ɪ\'læps]', 'v.逝去；过去 n.（光阴）逝去', '1. Five months have elapsed since he joined the army. 自从他参军以后,已经五个月了。 2. Three years have elapsed since we met last time. 我们上次相见至今已经三年了。 3. Fifteen minutes elapsed before the performance began. 过了15分钟演出才开始。 4. They met again after an elapse of many years. 他们多年后又相逢。', '过去式: elapsed 过去分词: elapsed 现在分词: elapsing 第三人称单数: elapses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('steep', '[stiːp]', 'adj.险峻的；陡峭的；急剧的、大起大落的 v.浸泡，浸透，湿透；沉浸，笼罩', '1. This hill is too steep to ride up on a bicycle. 这山太陡了，骑自行车可上不去。 2. The last part of the ascent is very steep. 最后一段上坡路很陡。 3. The bus toiled up the steep hill. 公共汽车艰难地爬上陡峭的山岗。 4. It’s priced at fifty pounds, and I think that’s a bit steep for a secondhand lawn mower. 那东西标价50英镑，而我认为对于一部二手货的割草机来说，那个价钱不合理。', '副词: steeply 比较级: steeper 最高级: steepest 名词: steepness 过去式: steeped 过去分词: steeped 现在分词: steeping 第三人称单数: steeps');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accessory', '[ək\'sesəri]', 'n.附件；配件；同谋 adj.辅助的；附属的；同谋的', '1. He asked me to buy him some accessories for a car. 他让我给他买些汽车附件。 2. Every item shall include a standard complement of accessories and special tools to ensure the normal operation. 为保证设备的正常运转，每个品目都应包括一套标准定额的附件和专用工具。 3. This silk scarf is the perfect accessory for stylish summer evenings. 这条丝绸围巾对于这个时髦的夏日夜晚,是再合适不过的配件了。 4. He is Tom\'s accessory. 他是汤姆的帮凶。 5. He was using his accessory muscles of respiration. 他在用呼吸辅助肌进行呼吸。', '形容词: accessorial 副词: accessorily 名词: accessoriness 名词复数: accessories');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('plankton', '[\'plæŋktən]', 'n.浮游生物', '1. Plankton is at the bottom of the marine food chain. 浮游生物处于海洋食物链的最底层。', '形容词: planktonic');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('perish', '[\'perɪʃ]', 'vi.毁灭；消失；腐烂 vt.毁灭；使死亡', '1. We must plan our civilization or we must perish. 我们必须规划我们的文明，否则我们必定毁灭。 2. Almost a hundred people perished in the hotel fire last night. 近百人在昨夜旅馆的大火中丧生。 3. The ancient Aztec culture has all perished now. 古代阿兹台克文化现在已经全部消亡了。 4. Even the best quality rubber will perish with age. 就是最佳质量的橡胶也会因老化而腐烂。 5. Oil on your car tyres will perish them. 在你车胎上的油将会使车胎损坏。', '过去式: perished 过去分词: perished 现在分词: perishing 第三人称单数: perishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('impute', '[ɪm\'pjuːt]', 'v.归罪于；负责任；嫁祸', '1. I impute his failure to laziness. 我把他的失败归咎于他的懒惰。 2. They imputed the accident to the driver\'s carelessness. 他们把事故归咎于驾驶员的疏忽。 3. Don\'t impute to me that you failed. 不要把失败的责任推到我身上。 4. He was innocent of the crime imputed to him. 对于所加在他身上的罪，他是无辜的。', '过去式: imputed 过去分词: imputed 现在分词: imputing 第三人称单数: imputes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('lofty', '[\'lɔːfti]', 'adj.高的；崇高的；高尚的；傲慢的', '1. There are lofty fells behind this village. 这个村庄后面是高高的荒山。 2. Longer shadow falls from lofty mountain. 山高投影长。 3. They saw the lofty peak in all its majesty. 他们看到了高耸的山峰，气势雄伟壮丽。 4. He has lent his name to the lofty cause. 他以自己的名义支持这一崇高的事业。', '副词: loftily 比较级: loftier 最高级: loftiest 名词: loftiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('accustomed', '[ə\'kʌstəmd]', 'adj.习惯了的；通常的', '1. He was accustomed to command, not to entreat. 他习惯于发号施令，而不是恳求他人。 2. You will soon get accustomed to the climate here. 你会很快习惯这里的气候的。 3. I might have been incredulous had I not been accustomed to such responses. 若非我已经习惯了这样的回答，我可能不敢轻易相信。 4. He is accustom to get up at six. 他习惯于6点起床。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('welfare', '[\'welfer]', 'n.福利；福利事业；幸福', '1. The welfare of the individual is bound up with the welfare of the community. 个人的福利与社会的福利有着密切的关系。 2. These are matters that bear on the welfare of the community. 这些都是与社会福利有关的问题。 3. The government decided to promote public welfare. 政府决定发展公共福利。 4. My principal concern is my family\'s welfare. 我至为关心的是我一家的幸福。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bubble', '[\'bʌbl]', 'n.气泡；泡影 v.起泡；冒泡；充满...感情', '1. A bubble will burst at the slightest touch. 气泡稍微一碰就破。 2. As a stock market bubble is taking shape, the investors should take precautions against the risks. 股市泡沫正在形成,投资者应该防范风险。 3. His hope vanished like a bubble. 他的希望化作泡影。 4. He didn\'t want to burst the newcomer\'s bubble. 他不想打破这个新来者的不切实际的美梦。 5. The water in the pan was beginning to bubble. 锅里的水开始起泡。', '过去式: bubbled 过去分词: bubbled 现在分词: bubbling 第三人称单数: bubbles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('apparel', '[ə\'pærəl]', 'n.衣服；装具 vt.装饰；使 ... 穿衣', '1. Apparel make the man. 人靠衣装，佛靠金装。 2. Her wedding apparel is made by a very famous fashion designer. 她的结婚礼服是由一位非常著名的时装设计师制作的。 3. His house is tastefully appareled. 他的房子装帧雅致。', '过去式: appareled/apparelled 过去分词: appareled/apparelled 现在分词: appareling/apparelling 第三人称单数: apparels');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idiom', '[\'ɪdiəm]', 'n.成语；惯用语；方言；风格；特色', '1. This idiom cannot be translated literally. 这个成语无法照字面翻译。 2. From that story comes the idiom \"Draw a snake and add feet to it\". “画蛇添足”这个成语就是从这个故事来的。 3. \"Let the cat out of the bag\" is an idiom meaning to tell a secret by mistake. “让猫从袋子里跑出来”是惯用语，意思是无意中泄露秘密。 4. He spoke in the idiom of the New England countryside. 他讲新英格兰乡下的方言。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rigorous', '[\'rɪɡərəs]', 'adj.严格的；严厉的；严峻的；细致的', '1. The planes have to undergo rigorous safety checks. 这些飞机得接受非常严格的安全检查。 2. The work failed to meet their rigorous standards. 工作没有达到他们的严格标准。 3. It further implements the safe production responsibility system, and enforces rigorous safe production laws and regulations and a related accountability system. 进一步实行安全生产责任体系，加强严厉的安全生产法规和相关责任体系。 4. He lived through the rigorous trials of revolutionary war. 他经受了革命战争的严峻考验。', '副词: rigorously 名词: rigorousness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('haggle', '[\'hæɡl]', 'vi.争论；讨价还价 vt.乱砍 n.讨价还价；争论', '1. It\'s not worth haggling over a few pence. 为几便士争论不休实在不值得。 2. He preferred to be overcharged than to haggle. 他宁愿被”宰”也不愿讨价还价。 3. You can haggle with the best of them. 能和最厉害的人讨价还价。 4. In many countries you have to haggle before you buy anything. 在许多国家里买东西之前都得讨价还价。', '名词: haggler 过去式: haggled 过去分词: haggled 现在分词: haggling 第三人称单数: haggles');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('station', '[\'steɪʃn]', 'n.站；火车站；电视台；社会地位；牧羊场；驻地；岗位 v.驻扎；安置', '1. Don\'t forget to drop by at the gas station. 别忘了到煤气站去看看。 2. He was walking up and down the station platform. 他在火车站的月台上走来走去。 3. Can you tell me the way to the railway station? 你能告诉我往火车站的路怎么走吗？ 4. Which TV station is the programme on? 这个节目在哪家电视台播放? 5. Guards were stationed around the prison. 卫兵派驻在监狱四周。', '过去式: stationed 过去分词: stationed 现在分词: stationing 第三人称单数: stations');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('varnish', '[\'vɑːrnɪʃ]', 'n.油漆；掩饰；光泽面；指甲油 v.粉饰；涂油漆于；使光亮', '1. The varnish was made to imitate wood grain. 油漆刷出来像木纹。 2. She covers her selfishness with a varnish of good manners. 她用一种表面上很有礼貌的态度来掩饰她的自私。 3. The hot plate may spoil the varnish on the table. 这只热盘子会损坏桌面的光泽。 4. I chipped my nail varnish when I was cooking. 我烧菜的时候，指甲油脱落了。 5. He tried to varnish over the truth with a lie. 他试图用谎言来掩盖真相。', '名词: varnisher 过去式: varnished 过去分词: varnished 现在分词: varnishing 第三人称单数: varnishes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('pants', '[pænts]', 'n.裤子，短裤（名词pant的复数形式） v.气喘吁吁；渴望（动词pant的第三人称单数形式）', '1. He asked the tailor to make over his pants. 他请裁缝把他的裤子翻改了一下。 2. This jacket will match those pants nicely. 这件夹克和那条裤子会十分相配。 3. My old pair of pants has worn thin at the knees. 我那条旧裤子的膝盖处已穿薄了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('extemporaneous', '[ekˌstempə\'reɪnɪəs]', 'adj.即兴的；不用讲稿的；临时的；权宜的', '1. He made an extemporaneous speech. 他作了即席演说。 2. An accomplished extemporaneous speaker. 一位高明的即席演讲者 3. An extemporaneous policy decision. 一个权宜的政策决定 4. She made an extemporaneous speech on the ceremony. 她在典礼上做了一次即兴演讲。', '副词: extemporaneously 名词: extemporaneity');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('buddy', '[\'bʌdi]', 'n.伙伴；兄弟；好朋友 vi.结交', '1. Her driving buddy was in trouble. 她的开车伙伴出事了。 2. This is where you get off, buddy. 老兄，你在这里下车。 3. Buddy ,you need a litter change of pace. 哥们,你要换换口味啦。 4. He and I were buddies at school. 他和我在学校是好朋友。 5. You and your neighbour might want to buddy up to make the trip more enjoyable. 你同你的邻居或许想结伴旅游，热闹一点。', '名词复数: buddies 过去式: buddied 过去分词: buddied 现在分词: buddying 第三人称单数: buddies');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scrape', '[skreɪp]', 'v.刮掉；擦掉 n.擦伤；擦掉；刮擦声；<口>窘境', '1. I must have scraped some of the paint off when I was parking the car. 我准是停放汽车的时候刮掉了一些油漆。 2. He bent over to scrape some dirt off his shoes. 他弯腰刮掉鞋子上的尘土。 3. Scrape your shoes on the door mat before you come in. 进屋前先在门口擦鞋垫上擦一擦鞋子。 4. He suffered a few cuts and scrapes. 他割破和擦伤了几个地方。', '过去式: scraped 过去分词: scraped 现在分词: scraping 第三人称单数: scrapes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('humidity', '[hjuː\'mɪdəti]', 'n.湿度；湿气', '1. My laundry will not dry because of the humidity. 由于湿度关系，我的衣物无法晾干。 2. Humidity is a measure of moisture in the atmosphere. 湿度是空气内含水分多少的量度。 3. It\'s said by forecast that the humidity in the air today is 60%. 据预报说今天的空气湿度是百分之六十。 4. Humidity caused me another fit of rheumatism. 湿气使我的风湿病又发作了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stature', '[\'stætʃər]', 'n.身高；名望', '1. She was rather small in stature. 她身材矮小。 2. He is five feet five inches in stature/height. 他身高5英尺5英寸。 3. She had not yet grown to full stature. 她的个子还没有完全长到应有的高度。 4. He is a musician of world stature. 他是一个世界级的音乐家。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('fiber', '[\'faɪbə]', 'n.纤维(物质)；性格；质地', '1. It was not until 1884 that the first artificial fiber was made. 直到一八八四年，第一个人造纤维才制造出来。 2. Scientists are recommending that people eat more fiber. 科学家建议人们多吃些纤维素。 3. He is a man of real fiber. 他是一个有骨气的男子。 4. I love my country with every fiber of my being. 我深爱我的祖国。', '形容词: fibered');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('hibernation', '[ˌhaɪbə\'neɪʃn]', 'n.冬眠', '1. Hibernation has long intrigued biologists. 冬眠长期以来一直引起生物学家的兴趣。 2. Some animals can overwinter without the hibernation. 有些动物不需要冬眠也能过冬。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('nostalgia', '[nə\'stældʒə]', 'n.乡愁；向往过去；怀旧之情', '1. The soldiers were filled with nostalgia. 士兵们心中充满了乡愁。 2. The familiar and echoing sound of pianos from Gulangyu is his nostalgia. 那回荡着的熟悉的鼓浪屿钢琴声就是他的乡愁。 3. The sight inspired him with nostalgia. 这景象激起了他的怀旧之情。 4. Her work is pervaded by nostalgia for a past age. 她的作品充满了怀旧之情。', '形容词: nostalgic 副词: nostalgically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('venture', '[\'ventʃər]', 'n.冒险(事业)；风险；投机；企业 v.冒险；敢于；冒昧地说', '1. All our hopes rested upon this venture. 我们所有的希望都寄托在这次冒险上了。 2. These foreigners have put forward a proposal for a joint venture. 这些外国人提出了一个合资企业的建议。 3. The hi-tech industry attracts much venture capital. 高科技产业吸引着许多风险投资。 4. Any business venture contains an element of risk. 任何商业投资都包含一定的风险因素。 5. Don\'t venture into the jungle without a guide 如果没有向导,就不要冒险到森林里去。', '名词: venturer 过去式: ventured 过去分词: ventured 现在分词: venturing 第三人称单数: ventures');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annotate', '[\'ænəteɪt]', 'v.注解', '1. As an option, you can annotate recorded movies with text. 如一项选择，你能够以文本给被记载的电影作注解。 2. I might want to go back and annotate this document with metadata specific to its production. 我可能希望返回去并使用针对其研究成果的元数据注解该文档。', '形容词: annotative 名词: annotator 过去式: annotated 过去分词: annotated 现在分词: annotating 第三人称单数: annotates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('prevail', '[prɪ\'veɪl]', 'vi.盛行；获胜；劝说', '1. This old custom does not prevail now. 这种旧风俗现在已经不流行了。 2. Misty weather prevails in this part of the country. 该国的这一地区天气多雾。 3. Virtue will prevail against evil. 美德定将战胜邪恶。 4. I tried to prevail on him to stay. 我曾试图说服他留下。', '名词: prevailer 过去式: prevailed 过去分词: prevailed 现在分词: prevailing 第三人称单数: prevails');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('persist', '[pər\'sɪst]', 'v.坚持；执意；继续；持续', '1. I hope you\'ll persist in your efforts. 我希望你们再接再励。 2. He will persist in riding that dreadful bicycle. 他执意要骑那辆破自行车。 3. If you persist, you will annoy them even more. 你若固执，他们就更恼火了。 4. If you persist in breaking the law you will go to prison. 如果你再继续违法的话，你会坐牢的。', '名词: persister 过去式: persisted 过去分词: persisted 现在分词: persisting 第三人称单数: persists');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('idyllic', '[aɪ\'dɪlɪk]', 'adj.田园诗的；田园的', '1. Don\'t you think that sounds idyllic? 你不觉得那听起来很富有诗情画意吗? 2. This idyllic pastoral scene is only part of the picture. 这充满诗意的田园景色只是画面的一角。 3. To an outsider this looks like an idyllic life. 在局外人看来这好像是一种田园式的生活。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gross', '[ɡroʊs]', 'adj.总的；粗鲁的；公然的；荒唐的；令人讨厌的 n.总量；总额 vt.总共赚得 adv.总共地', '1. The gross national product had increased 5 percent last year. 去年的国民生产总值提高了百分之五。 2. You can tell from his gross language that the man was uneducated. 从他那粗俗的语言可以看出，这个人没受过教育。 3. They were accused of gross negligence. 他们因公然渎职而被指控。 4. That is a gross distortion of the truth. 这是对真相的荒唐歪曲。 5. The goods are to be sold by the gross. 这些货物是要趸批出售的。 6. The new movie grossed an estimated $36.4 million at the box office. 这部新电影总共收获了3640万美元的票房成绩。 7. He earned $60,000 gross. 他总共赚了6万美元。', '副词: grossly 比较级: grosser 最高级: grossest 名词: grosser 过去式: grossed 过去分词: grossed 现在分词: grossing 第三人称单数: grosses');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('seemingly', '[\'siːmɪŋli]', 'adv.表面上；似乎；看起来', '1. Any seemingly viable proposition will be tested by market research. 任何表面上可行的建议都要通过市场研究予以检验。 2. The utility, though seemingly rebuffed, in fact got what it wanted, or thereabouts. 公司虽然表面上遭到了挫败，实际上得到了它所要求的，或者相差不多的增额。 3. She plays with seemingly effortless skill. 她演奏得似乎毫不费力。 4. He is seemingly to have lost enthusiasm in reading. 他似乎在阅读上已经失去了热情。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('abduct', '[æb\'dʌkt]', 'vt.诱拐；绑走', '1. He had attempted to abduct the two children. 他曾企图诱拐这两名儿童。 2. I can say you abduct a high school student. 我可以告你诱拐中学生。', '名词: abduction 过去式: abducted 过去分词: abducted 现在分词: abducting 第三人称单数: abducts');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('embryo', '[\'embrioʊ]', 'n.胚胎；萌芽', '1. They are engaging in an embryo research. 他们正在进行一项胚胎研究。 2. The embryo develops into a fetus. 胚胎发育成胎儿。 3. The embryo and childhood of dance can be traced back to the first days of human beings, far exceeding human memory. 舞蹈的萌芽和形成时间，可以远溯到人类发展的洪荒时期，远远超出了人类的记忆范围。', '名词复数: embryos');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('rare', '[rer]', 'adj.罕见的；珍贵的；煎得嫩的', '1. It is rare to find such a genius nowadays. 这样的天才现在很少见。 2. It was in the days when motorcars were rare. 那是在汽车还罕见的时代。 3. He\'s devoted his whole life to the protection of the rare animals. 他终生献身于珍稀动物的保护。 4. Those rare books are shelved in the East Library. 那些珍贵的书籍都放在图书馆东馆的架子上。', '比较级: rarer 最高级: rarest 名词: rareness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('skeptic', '[\'skeptɪk]', 'n.怀疑者；怀疑论者；无神论者', '1. And, most importantly to the skeptic, Jesus did all this in history. 而，最能取信于怀疑者的一点是，耶稣确实在历史上做过这些事情。 2. The slender skeptic skips school in slack seasons, which signifies her slackness. 一到淡季那个苗条的怀疑者就逃学，这表现了她的懒散。 3. A skeptic might yawn.After all, genetic engineering isn\'t new. 怀疑论者对这种工作也许会想打哈欠，毕竟遗传工程已非新鲜事了。 4. If you were a skeptic and needed proof, well, now you have it! 如果你是一个凡事求证的怀疑论者，现在你可以找到证明了！', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('annihilate', '[ə\'naɪəleɪt]', 'v.消灭；歼灭；彻底消除；使无效；废止', '1. Identify the enemy you wish to annihilate. 只管标记你要消灭的敌人。 2. The United States cannot annihilate the Chinese nation with its small stack of atom bombs. 美国那点原子弹，消灭不了中国人。 3. We must herd the enemy troops together and annihilate them. 我们必须聚敌而歼灭之。', '形容词: annihilable 名词: annihilability 过去式: annihilated 过去分词: annihilated 现在分词: annihilating 第三人称单数: annihilates');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tow', '[toʊ]', 'v.拖；拉；牵引 n.拖；拽；拖绳', '1. We have to tow that car to the nearest garage. 我们不得不把汽车拖到最近的修车厂。 2. The ship needed two tugs to tow it into port. 这艘船需用两艘拖船把它拖进港。 3. The broken-down car was taken in tow by a lorry. 一辆卡车拉着一辆坏了的汽车。 4. When she sits at the beach, Greenpeace tries to tow her back into the ocean. 你妈妈胖到她座在沙滩上时，绿色和平组织会尝试著把她拉回大海里。 5. My car\'s broken down; will you give me a tow? 我的车抛锚了，能用你的车给我拖一拖吗？', '形容词: towable 名词: tower 过去式: towed 过去分词: towed 现在分词: towing 第三人称单数: tows');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('scruffy', '[\'skrʌfi]', 'adj.邋遢的；肮脏的；破旧的', '1. You can\'t go to a job interview looking so scruffy! 你求职去面试不能这邋里邋遢的！ 2. His scruffy appearance does not reflect his character. 他邋遢的外表并不反映他的性格。 3. She was wearing a scruffy pair of jeans. 她穿着一条脏兮兮的牛仔裤。 4. It is not proper to wear a scruffy jeans in a dinner party. 穿着破旧的牛仔裤在宴会上显得不太得体。', '副词: scruffily 比较级: scruffier 最高级: scruffiest 名词: scruffiness');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('advent', '[\'ædvent]', 'n.出现；到来', '1. The advent of the computer changed people\'s life greatly. 计算机的出现极大地改变了人们的生活。 2. With the advent of the rockets, the Space Age began. 随着火箭的出现,太空时代开始了。 3. The advent of the Euro will redefine Europe. 欧元的出现将重新定义欧洲。 4. With the advent of spring, everything comes to life again. 随着春天的到来，万物复苏了。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('proofread', '[\'pruːfriːd]', 'vt.校对', '1. It\'s a part of your duties to proofread. 校对是你的份内之事。 2. Proofread them for content and spelling. 就内容和拼写进行校对。', '名词: proofreader 过去式: proofread 过去分词: proofread 现在分词: proofreading 第三人称单数: proofreads');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('meantime', '[\'miːntaɪm]', 'adv.与此同时 n.同时；其间', '1. I continued working. Meantime, he went out shopping. 我继续工作。这期间他出去买东西。 2. The new software will be available in the spring. Meantime, users with problems can call our helpline. 今年春天,用户可以使用新的软件。与此同时,用户如有问题可致电我们的热线服务。 3. I like skiing and in the meantime, I know it is very dangerous. 我喜欢滑雪，同时也知道这非常危险。 4. You buy the fruits, in the meantime I\'ll cook breakfast. 你去买水果，同时我来做早餐。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('antiseptic', '[ˌænti\'septɪk]', 'n.杀菌剂；防腐剂 adj.杀菌的；防腐的；极为干净整洁的；冷漠的', '1. Antiseptic is used to sterilize the skin before giving an injection. 杀菌剂被用于在注射前给皮肤消毒。 2. They\'re doing tests to evaluate the effectiveness of this herb as an antiseptic. 他们正在检测这种草药作为杀菌剂的有效性。 3. We garantee that no artifical antiseptic in our food. 我们生产的所有食品保证不含人造防腐剂。 4. Ca-propionate was used as antiseptic agent to restrain growth of bacteria and mold. 并通过添加丙酸钙作为防腐剂有效抑制了细菌和霉菌的生长。 5. It is said that marjoram has antiseptic qualities. 据说马郁兰有杀菌的特性。', '副词: antiseptically');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('treason', '[\'triːzn]', 'n.叛逆 通敌 背叛 叛国罪', '1. He was executed for treason. 他因叛国罪已处死。 2. He was beheaded for high treason. 他因叛国罪被斩首。 3. English politician and historian who was falsely accused of treason and banished(1667). While in France he wrote his major work, The History of the Rebellion and Civil Wars in England(1702-1704). 克拉伦登英国政治家和历史学家，被错判叛国罪并流放(1667年)。在法国写出他的重要著作英国叛乱和内战史(1702－1704年) 4. They have committed treason against the state. 他们已犯了叛国罪。', 'none');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('tantalize', '[\'tæntəlaɪz]', 'v.（以可望而不可即之物）逗引或招惹（人或动物）；使着急', '1. Give the dog the bone don\'t tantalize him. 把那块骨头给那条狗吧--别让它乾著急了。 2. He was tantalized by visions of power and wealth. 他追求不到可望而不可即的权力和财富，受尽了折磨。', '副词: tantalizingly 名词: tantalization 过去式: tantalized 过去分词: tantalized 现在分词: tantalizing 第三人称单数: tantalizes');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('gorge', '[ɡɔːrdʒ]', 'n.峡谷；咽喉；大量食物；饱食；阻碍物；厌恶 vt.暴食；贪婪地吞咽 vi.狼吞虎咽', '1. A deep gorge separates the two halves of the city. 有一道深谷把这座城市分成两部分。 2. Have you been to the Yangtse Gorges? 你去过长江三峡吗？ 3. His gorge was stuck by a fish bone. 鱼刺卡在他的咽喉。 4. An ice gorge has blocked the shipping lane. 冰块阻碍了航道。 5. The fat man gorged himself constantly with enormous desserts. 那个胖子经常大吃甜食。 6. The boy gorged on turkey on Christmas Day. 这男孩耶诞节那天大吃火鸡。', '名词: gorger 过去式: gorged 过去分词: gorged 现在分词: gorging 第三人称单数: gorges');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('stratum', '[\'streɪtəm]', 'n.地层；阶层', '1. They represent each society stratum. 他们代表各个社会阶层。 2. Such inequalities are found in every stratum. 这类不公平的现象存在于社会的每一个阶层。', '形容词: stratal 名词复数: strata');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('bark', '[bɑːrk]', 'v.(狗)吠；咆哮 v.剥皮；擦伤 n.狗吠；咆哮 n.树皮', '1. The dog barked when the stranger came near. 当陌生人走近时，狗叫了起来。 2. An old dog does not bark for nothing. 老狗不会无事而吠。 3. When you speak to people, don\'t bark at them. 当你和人说话时不要咆哮。 4. Some officers bark out their orders. 有些军官以粗暴的声音发布命令。 5. He barked his elbow on the wall. 他碰到墙上，肘部擦破了皮。 6. Those trees have very beautiful white bark. 那些树长着非常漂亮的白色树皮。', '过去式: barked 过去分词: barked 现在分词: barking 第三人称单数: barks');
INSERT INTO `toefl` VALUES ('arrogance', '[\'ærəɡəns]', 'n.傲慢；自大', '1. I disliked him for his arrogance. 我讨厌他的傲慢。 2. It is easy to misconstrue confidence as arrogance. 很容易将信心误解为傲慢。 3. The biggest failure of life is arrogance! 人生最大的失败是自大！ 4. The arrogance spells danger and may signal the beginning of a crisis. 自大便是危机的开端，此时国家将危在旦夕。', 'none');
